INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('abelone', 'Abelone is a hardworking Nord woman who serves as the primary laborer at the Windpeak Inn in Dawnstar, maintaining its daily operations through various physical tasks. Her reliable presence and strong work ethic make her an essential part of the inn''s functioning, though she maintains a humble and practical approach to her duties.', 'nord, innkeeper, pale', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh climate of The Pale, Abelone found steady employment at the Windpeak Inn after demonstrating her capability for hard physical labor and reliability. Having lived through the difficulties of Dawnstar''s notorious nightmare plague, she has developed a pragmatic outlook on life and values the stability her position at the inn provides.', 'Abelone exhibits the typical Nord traits of industriousness and straightforwardness, approaching her work with dedication and without complaint. She maintains a professional demeanor with visitors while showing loyalty to her employer, though she prefers to defer official business to Thoring. Her consistent routine and dedication to manual labor suggest a person who finds satisfaction in honest work and maintaining order.', 'Abelone possesses the sturdy build typical of Nord women, with strong arms and callused hands from years of physical labor. Her weather-worn features reflect a life spent working outdoors in Dawnstar''s harsh climate, while her posture remains straight and strong despite the demanding nature of her work.', '* Thoring - Employer and innkeeper whom she respects and defers to for business matters * Inn Regulars - Maintains cordial but professional relationships with frequent patrons * Local Townspeople - Known as a reliable worker and familiar face in the community * Fellow Inn Workers - Cooperates with other staff to maintain the establishment', 'Abelone serves as the primary laborer at the Windpeak Inn, responsible for essential maintenance tasks including woodcutting, carrying firewood, and tending to the chicken pen. Her role is crucial for keeping the inn operational, particularly during Dawnstar''s harsh winters when regular firewood supply is essential for guests'' comfort.', '* Experienced in physical labor and maintenance tasks * Proficient with basic tools including the grindstone and woodcutting axe * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Knowledgeable in animal husbandry, particularly chicken-keeping * Skilled at managing time and maintaining a strict work schedule', 'Abelone speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nords, preferring brief, practical statements over lengthy conversation. Her tone is polite but businesslike, often directing visitors to Thoring for any official inn business.', '* Maintain her position of responsibility at the Windpeak Inn * Continue providing reliable service to ensure the inn''s smooth operation * Preserve her reputation as a dependable worker in Dawnstar');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('acolyte_jenssen', 'Acolyte Jenssen is a devoted Nord priest of Kynareth who serves as a dedicated healer at the Temple of Kynareth in Whiterun. His gentle demeanor and unwavering commitment to helping the sick and injured make him an invaluable member of the temple''s healing staff, particularly during times of civil unrest when his services are most needed.', 'nord, priest, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun Hold, Jenssen felt called to Kynareth''s service from an early age, drawn to her aspects of healing and nature. He completed his religious training under the guidance of senior priests at the Temple of Kynareth, where he developed his restoration magic abilities and learned the healing arts. His dedication during the difficult years of the civil war has proven him to be an essential caregiver to Whiterun''s citizens.', 'Jenssen exhibits a calm, patient, and nurturing disposition that perfectly suits his role as a healer. He approaches his duties with quiet dedication and shows genuine concern for his patients'' wellbeing, often offering words of comfort alongside magical healing. Despite the chaos of war around him, he maintains an inner serenity that reflects his deep spiritual connection to Kynareth.', 'A middle-aged Nord with weathered features that reflect his Nordic heritage and years of dedicated service. His face shows gentle laugh lines around his eyes, and his hands bear the careful, precise movements of an experienced healer. His posture is straight but relaxed, reflecting both his religious discipline and approachable nature.', '* Danica Pure-Spring - Respected superior and fellow healer at the Temple * Ahlam - Colleague and fellow healer who shares his dedication to the sick * Temple Patients - Maintains caring, professional relationships with those under his care * Citizens of Whiterun - Well-regarded member of the community, especially among those he''s helped heal', 'As an Acolyte at the Temple of Kynareth, Jenssen''s primary duties involve healing the sick and injured using restoration magic and traditional medicine. He maintains a regular schedule of patient care, temple maintenance, and prayer, while also helping to repair temple damages during times of conflict.', '* Highly practiced in Restoration magic, particularly healing spells * Competent in defensive magic including Oakflesh * Basic proficiency in destruction magic (Lightning-based spells) * Experienced in traditional medicine and patient care * Knowledge of temple rites and religious ceremonies * Basic construction and repair abilities', 'Speaks in a gentle, soothing tone that puts patients at ease, using simple but encouraging words. His manner of speech reflects both his Nordic heritage and his religious training, with frequent references to rest, patience, and healing.', '* Continue serving Kynareth by healing those in need and maintaining her temple * Help preserve the Temple of Kynareth through the civil war and its aftermath * Guide and mentor future healers in Kynareth''s ways * Bring comfort and healing to as many people as possible');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('addvar', 'Addvar is a hardworking Nord fishmonger in Solitude who prioritizes providing for his family during difficult times. Despite personal tragedy with his brother-in-law''s execution, he maintains a pragmatic approach to life while balancing his roles as a devoted father, supportive husband, and reliable merchant.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Addvar learned the fishing trade from a young age, working the docks and eventually establishing his own fish stall in the marketplace. His life was significantly impacted by the execution of his brother-in-law Roggvir, forcing him to navigate both personal tragedy and the political tensions in Solitude while maintaining his family''s livelihood.', 'Addvar exhibits a practical, no-nonsense attitude that stems from his working-class background and focus on survival. He shows compassion and wisdom in his parenting, demonstrated by his handling of difficult situations with his daughter Svari, while maintaining strong moral principles about honesty and accountability.', 'A weathered Nord of average height and build, with the muscular arms and calloused hands typical of someone who works daily with fishing nets and heavy catches. His face shows the effects of long hours working outdoors in Solitude''s harsh climate.', '* Greta - His wife who helps run the fish stall and maintains their household * Svari - His young daughter whom he strives to protect and raise with strong values * Roggvir - His executed brother-in-law, whose death has impacted the family deeply * Jala - Fellow merchant in Solitude''s marketplace * East Empire Company workers - Tense relationship due to competition for fishing spots * Red Wave crew - Hostile relationship due to territorial disputes at the docks', 'Addvar works as a fishmonger in Solitude''s marketplace, maintaining a stall that operates for fourteen hours daily. His duties include fishing at the docks, preparing and preserving his catch, and selling fresh fish to the city''s residents.', '* Experienced fisherman capable of finding the best fishing spots around Solitude''s docks * Knowledgeable about various types of fish and their preparation * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Skilled at haggling and merchant trades * Proficient at maintaining and repairing fishing equipment', 'Addvar speaks in a direct, straightforward manner typical of working-class Nords, frequently calling out to promote his wares. His speech reflects his practical nature, using simple language focused on business and family matters.', '* Provide a stable income for his family despite challenging political and economic circumstances * Protect and properly raise his daughter Svari despite the family''s recent trauma * Maintain and potentially expand his fishing business while navigating conflicts with competitors * Help his wife Greta cope with the loss of her brother while keeping the family together');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('addvild', 'Addvild is a dedicated Nord farmer who has earned the trust of the prominent Snow-Shod family to manage their farm near Riften. A hardworking and practical man, he balances his duties as both a farmer and husband while maintaining a cautious awareness of the dangers that lurk beyond the farm''s boundaries.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally a common laborer in the Rift, Addvild proved himself through years of honest work until earning the Snow-Shods'' trust to manage their farm. His marriage to Leonara Arius, who had previously lost her family, marks a significant turning point in his life and has given him additional purpose in protecting both his livelihood and loved ones.', 'Addvild is pragmatic and diligent, demonstrating unwavering dedication to his work while maintaining a humble appreciation for the trust placed in him by the Snow-Shods. He shows a tender, protective side with his wife Leonara, balancing optimism with practical caution regarding their safety, and prefers to focus on his immediate responsibilities rather than dwelling on larger political concerns.', 'As a Nord farmer who spends long days working the land, Addvild possesses a sturdy, weather-worn physique typical of his race. His hands are calloused from years of agricultural labor, and his skin shows the effects of constant exposure to the elements.', '* Leonara Arius - Beloved wife who shares his work on the farm and whom he strives to protect * Vulwulf Snow-Shod - Respected employer who has shown great trust in his abilities * Snow-Shod Family - Employers who he believes would come to his aid if needed * Riften Guards - Appreciated protectors of the farm whom he relies on for security', 'Addvild serves as the primary caretaker of Snow-Shod Farm, managing all aspects of the agricultural operation including crop cultivation and animal husbandry. His position involves maintaining the farm''s productivity, purchasing additional crops from travelers, and ensuring the property''s security.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Capable of basic combat with a dagger for self-defense * Proficient in animal husbandry and farm management * Basic trading and negotiation skills for purchasing crops from travelers', 'Addvild speaks in a straightforward, honest manner typical of Nord farmers, showing respect for authority while maintaining a practical outlook. His speech often reflects his appreciation for his position and concern for his wife''s wellbeing.', '* Maintain the prosperity and security of Snow-Shod Farm to justify the trust placed in him * Build a safe and happy life with his wife Leonara * Protect their farm from potential threats while avoiding involvement in larger political conflicts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('adeber', 'Adeber is a reclusive Breton miner at Left Hand Mine who demonstrates an almost obsessive dedication to his work, refusing to take breaks or engage in social activities. His singular focus on mining and complete devotion to his labor suggests a deeper psychological drive or past trauma that compels him to work endlessly.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Adeber likely came to Skyrim seeking opportunity in its rich mining industry. His complete absorption in work and reluctance to engage with others hints at a possible tragic past or personal loss that drove him to seek solitude in the remote mines near Markarth.', 'Adeber exhibits signs of obsessive-compulsive behavior, demonstrated by his inability to break from his mining routine even for basic needs like eating or sleeping. His gruff demeanor and minimal social interaction suggest either deep-seated trauma or a natural inclination toward solitude, while his singular focus on work indicates possible anxiety about idleness.', 'A weathered Breton of average height with the muscular build typical of someone engaged in constant physical labor. His hands are calloused and scarred from years of mining, and his posture shows the slight stoop common to career miners.', '* Bothela - Occasional customer who purchases ore for her alchemy shop * Left Hand Mine Workers - Maintains minimal professional contact * Pavo Attius - Mine owner and employer, interaction limited to work matters * Skaggi Scar-Face - Fellow miner with whom he shares workspace but minimal conversation', 'Adeber works as a full-time miner at Left Hand Mine, extracting various ores from the mine''s rich veins. His role appears to be entirely self-directed, with no breaks or supervision needed to maintain his constant work output.', '* Expert mining technique developed through years of continuous practice * Advanced knowledge of ore identification and extraction methods * Physical endurance that allows for continuous work without rest * Basic understanding of mine safety and structural integrity', 'Speaks in short, clipped sentences with a brusque tone that discourages further conversation. His vocabulary is simple and utilitarian, focused entirely on work-related matters.', '* Continue his uninterrupted mining work without distraction or interference * Maintain his solitary lifestyle away from social obligations * Extract as much ore as possible from the mine''s depths');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('adelaisa_vendicci', 'Adelaisa Vendicci is a stern and efficient Imperial administrator for the East Empire Company, serving as their chief inspector in Skyrim. She is a no-nonsense professional known for her military background and expertise in both commerce and combat, particularly in dealing with maritime threats to trade operations.', 'imperial, peasant, haafingar, legion, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Adelaisa served in the Imperial Legion before transitioning to a role with the East Empire Company. Her military experience and sharp business acumen led to her rapid advancement within the company''s hierarchy, eventually earning her position as a senior inspector overseeing operations in Skyrim''s port cities.', 'Direct, efficient, and sometimes abrasive, Adelaisa has little patience for incompetence or excuses. She maintains high standards for herself and others, approaching her duties with military precision and discipline. Though stern, she shows genuine appreciation for those who demonstrate competence and reliability in their work.', 'A fit, middle-aged Imperial woman with the bearing of a veteran soldier. Her face bears the weathered look of someone who spends considerable time at sea, with sharp, observant eyes and an expression that suggests constant vigilance.', '* Orthus Endario - Subordinate whom she frequently criticizes for poor management * East Empire Company Senior Leadership - Respected superior officers who trust her judgment * Blood Horkers - Enemy pirates she actively works to eliminate * Ship Captains and Dock Workers - Professional relationships maintained through authority and respect', 'Senior Inspector for the East Empire Company, responsible for overseeing trading operations and security in Skyrim''s major ports. She conducts regular inspections of company facilities, investigates threats to trade routes, and coordinates military responses to pirate activities.', '* Experienced swordsman with Imperial Legion training * Expert in maritime trade operations and logistics * Skilled negotiator and administrator * Proficient in naval combat tactics and anti-piracy operations * Natural leadership abilities honed through military service', 'Speaks in clear, direct statements with a commanding tone that reflects her military background. Her vocabulary is precise and professional, often employing maritime and trade terminology.', '* Eliminate the Blood Horker threat and secure East Empire Company trading routes * Restore efficiency and profitability to the Windhelm office * Maintain the Company''s dominance in maritime trade throughout Skyrim * Establish stronger security measures against future pirate threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('adisla', 'Adisla is a hardworking elderly Nord farmer who has dedicated her later years to working at Hlaalu Farm, notable for being one of the few Nords willing to work for a Dunmer employer in the prejudiced city of Windhelm. Despite her advancing age, she maintains a strong work ethic and practical approach to life, while navigating the unique social dynamics of being a Nord employed by a Dark Elf in Skyrim''s most traditionalist hold.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Eastmarch, Adisla likely spent her entire life working farms in the harsh climate of northern Skyrim. She chose to work for Belyn Hlaalu despite the prevalent Nord-Dunmer tensions in Windhelm, suggesting either a more tolerant worldview or simply a practical need for steady employment. Her comments about aging indicate she has been working the land for many decades, possibly having started as a young woman.', 'Adisla is straightforward and practical, maintaining a strong work ethic despite her advancing age. While respectful of authority, she demonstrates quiet self-confidence in standing up for herself when criticized, particularly regarding her comfort needs. She shows a pragmatic attitude toward both work and social issues, neither fully embracing nor rejecting Windhelm''s prevalent racism.', 'Adisla is an elderly Nord woman, likely in her sixties or seventies, with the weathered features and strong build typical of someone who has spent a lifetime doing physical labor. Her body shows the effects of aging and years of farm work, though she maintains the hardy constitution characteristic of Nord farmers.', '* Belyn Hlaalu - Employer with whom she maintains a complex but generally positive working relationship * Captain Lonely-Gale - Shows dismissive attitude toward him, suggesting possible past negative interactions * Windhelm Citizens - Maintains distance from city politics while being aware of their curiosity about her working for a Dunmer * Endario - Indirect business contact through farm supply shipments', 'Adisla serves as the primary farmhand at Hlaalu Farm, responsible for daily cultivation and maintenance of the crops. Her duties include planting, harvesting, general farm maintenance, and ensuring the farmhouse remains in good condition. She works long hours from dawn to dusk, maintaining a strict daily routine that reflects her dedication to her responsibilities.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of crop cultivation in Skyrim''s harsh climate * Practical knowledge of farm maintenance and repair work * Basic combat abilities for self-defense with simple weapons * Skilled in cold-weather farming techniques and frost-resistant crop management', 'Adisla speaks in a direct, unembellished manner typical of Nord farmers, using practical terminology and occasionally showing dry wit. Her speech patterns reflect her working-class background while maintaining a respectful but firm tone with her employer.', '* Maintain her position at the farm while gradually reducing her workload as she ages * Secure a comfortable retirement after years of hard work * Preserve her independence and dignity while working under a younger employer * Continue proving that Nords and Dunmer can work together productively');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('adonato_leotelli', 'Adonato Leotelli is a passionate Imperial author and bard who has made Windhelm''s Candlehearth Hall his temporary residence and workplace. Despite the harsh political climate for Imperials in the Stormcloak capital, he perseveres in his mission to document and share the legendary tales of Skyrim, viewing storytelling as a vital force for inspiration in troubled times.', 'imperial, scholar, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Adonato traveled to Skyrim to study its rich oral traditions and legendary histories firsthand. He likely received formal training at the Imperial City''s Arcane University in historical documentation and literature before making his way north. The civil war and dragon crisis have complicated his work but also provided new material for his writings.', 'Adonato is an educated and eloquent individual who maintains a scholarly demeanor while remaining approachable and sociable. He demonstrates remarkable resilience by continuing his work in Windhelm despite the city''s anti-Imperial sentiment, showing both courage and dedication to his craft. Though sometimes melancholic about the loss of his assistant Isabella, he maintains an optimistic outlook about the power of storytelling to inspire hope.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the refined bearing typical of educated Cyrodilic citizens. His hands show the telltale ink stains of a writer, and his posture reflects long hours spent hunched over manuscripts. His face likely bears the weathered look of someone who has traveled extensively across Skyrim''s harsh landscape.', '* Giraud Gemane - Professional contact at the Bards College who eagerly awaits his works * Isabella - Former assistant whose loss he still mourns * Elda Early-Dawn - Owner of Candlehearth Hall who provides him lodging * Various Windhelm residents - Maintains cordial if sometimes tense relationships due to political climate', 'Adonato works as a professional author and historian, specializing in dramatizing Skyrim''s legends and historical events for contemporary audiences. He maintains connections with the Bards College in Solitude, suggesting he may hold some official position or fellowship with the institution. His daily routine revolves around writing, research, and gathering local stories and legends.', '* Accomplished writer and dramatist specializing in historical narratives * Trained bard with knowledge of Nordic legends and oral traditions * Basic self-defense capabilities with a dagger * Skilled researcher and interviewer * Diplomatic abilities necessary to survive as an Imperial in Stormcloak territory', 'Adonato speaks with the refined diction of an educated Imperial citizen, often incorporating literary references and poetic turns of phrase. His vocabulary is extensive but accessible, reflecting his profession as a writer who must connect with common readers while maintaining scholarly credibility.', '* Complete and publish his current work-in-progress despite recent setbacks * Document and preserve important Nordic legends and historical tales * Find a new assistant to help with research and writing * Establish himself as a preeminent chronicler of Skyrim''s legends * Navigate the political tensions in Windhelm while maintaining his professional integrity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('adrianne_avenicci', 'Adrianne Avenicci is a skilled Imperial blacksmith who represents the working class of Whiterun, balancing her craft with political influence through her father''s position as steward. She maintains a pragmatic approach to both business and relationships, running the successful Warmaiden''s shop while quietly advising her father on matters concerning the common folk of Whiterun.', 'imperial, blacksmith, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun as the daughter of Proventus Avenicci, Adrianne learned early on to balance nobility with practicality. She chose to pursue blacksmithing rather than follow her father into politics directly, though she maintains influence through him. She married Ulfberth War-Bear and together they established Warmaiden''s, building it into one of Whiterun''s most reliable armories.', 'Adrianne is hardworking, practical, and proud of her craft while remaining humble about her abilities compared to masters like Eorlund Gray-Mane. She shows political savvy in how she subtly influences Whiterun''s governance through her father while maintaining the appearance of a simple merchant. Despite her Imperial heritage, she''s well-integrated into Nord society and respected for her honest work ethic.', 'Adrianne is an Imperial woman in her early thirties with the strong build typical of a blacksmith. She has tanned skin from working the forge and calloused hands from years of metalworking. Her dark hair is usually pulled back practically from her face, which shows subtle signs of weathering from working outdoors.', '* Proventus Avenicci - Father and steward to the Jarl, whom she secretly advises * Ulfberth War-Bear - Husband and business partner who manages the shop''s interior * Jarl Balgruuf - Respects his leadership and influences his decisions through her father * Eorlund Gray-Mane - Acknowledges him as the superior smith while maintaining a professional rivalry * Citizens of Whiterun - Generally well-liked and respected by the community', 'Adrianne is the owner and primary blacksmith of Warmaiden''s, one of Whiterun''s principal armories. She manages the outdoor forge and weapons crafting while her husband handles indoor sales. Additionally, she serves as an unofficial advisor to her father on matters concerning Whiterun''s common folk.', '* Expert blacksmith specializing in weapons and armor crafting * Skilled businesswoman capable of managing a successful shop * Diplomatic abilities inherited from her father''s political background * Knowledge of military equipment and armor maintenance * Basic combat training with various weapons she crafts', 'Adrianne speaks directly and professionally, with the confidence of a successful merchant but without pretension. Her vocabulary reflects both her educated upbringing and her practical trade experience, allowing her to communicate effectively with both nobles and common folk.', '* Maintain and grow Warmaiden''s reputation as a reliable source of quality arms and armor * Continue influencing Whiterun''s governance through her father to benefit the working class * Improve her smithing skills to eventually rival the quality of the Skyforge * Ensure Whiterun''s prosperity and security through her trade');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('adril_arano', 'Adril Arano serves as Second Councilor of Raven Rock, acting as the right hand of Councilor Morvayn and chief of security for the settlement. A proud member of House Redoran, he embodies the stern dedication and unwavering loyalty characteristic of Dunmer nobility, while maintaining constant vigilance against threats to Raven Rock''s sovereignty.', 'darkelf, guard, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_adril', '', 'Born and raised within House Redoran''s hierarchical structure, Adril rose through the ranks through demonstrated loyalty and competence in administrative matters. He followed Councilor Morvayn to Solstheim when House Redoran took control of Raven Rock after the Empire''s withdrawal, helping to transform the failing Imperial settlement into a proper Dunmer colony. His years of service eventually earned him the position of Second Councilor, though the settlement''s struggles have made his duties increasingly challenging.', 'Adril is serious, cautious, and deeply suspicious of outsiders, reflecting years of dealing with threats to Raven Rock''s security. He maintains rigid adherence to duty and protocol, demonstrating unwavering loyalty to both Councilor Morvayn and House Redoran''s traditions. Despite his stern exterior, he shows genuine concern for Raven Rock''s citizens and shares a tender relationship with his wife Cindiri.', 'A mature Dunmer male with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race, carrying himself with the rigid posture of a disciplined official. His face bears the weathered features common to Dunmer who have spent years in Solstheim''s harsh climate, with sharp angular features and an ever-present look of stern attention.', '* Councilor Morvayn - Direct superior and object of unwavering loyalty * Cindiri Arano - Beloved wife despite their separate sleeping arrangements * House Redoran - Deeply committed member and representative * Raven Rock Guards - Direct authority over security forces * Severin Family - Initially trusted citizens who proved to be assassins * General population - Maintains professional but distant relationships with citizens', 'As Second Councilor of Raven Rock, Adril serves as both chief of security and primary administrative assistant to Councilor Morvayn. His duties include screening visitors, coordinating with the Redoran Guard, investigating threats to the settlement, and handling various administrative tasks that keep Raven Rock functioning.', '* Diplomatic expertise in handling official matters and maintaining political relationships * Administrative competence in managing settlement affairs * Basic combat training as befitting a House Redoran official * Investigation and security assessment capabilities * Knowledge of House Redoran law and customs', 'Speaks in a formal, authoritative manner befitting his station, often using stern tones when addressing outsiders. His vocabulary reflects his education and position, frequently emphasizing proper titles and official terminology.', '* Ensure the continued security and prosperity of Raven Rock * Protect Councilor Morvayn from any threats to his rule * Maintain House Redoran''s influence and traditions on Solstheim * Prevent any outside interference in Raven Rock''s sovereignty');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aduri_sarethi', 'Aduri Sarethi is a young, artistically-inclined Dark Elf farmer who feels trapped by her circumstances at Sarethi Farm. Despite her agricultural duties, she harbors dreams of becoming a painter and returning to her birthplace of Mournhold or exploring Skyrim''s grand cities.', 'darkelf, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born in Mournhold, Morrowind, Aduri relocated to Skyrim with her sister Avrusa following unknown circumstances, possibly related to the Red Year or the Argonian invasion. She was likely exposed to art and culture in her youth in Mournhold, which fostered her artistic aspirations and made the transition to rural farm life particularly difficult.', 'Aduri is restless, creative, and somewhat rebellious, often neglecting her farm duties due to boredom and resentment. She demonstrates a romantic, artistic temperament and yearns for cultural experiences beyond agricultural life. Her relationship with her sister is strained by the conflict between duty and dreams.', 'As a Dunmer, Aduri has the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her race. She appears younger than her sister Avrusa, with a frame suited to farm work but maintaining a graceful bearing typical of Dark Elves.', '* Avrusa Sarethi - Elder sister and caretaker, relationship strained by conflicting life goals * Uncle Sinderion - Deceased relative who was a master alchemist * Residents of Shor''s Stone - Maintains minimal social connections with nearby townsfolk', 'Aduri works as a farmer at Sarethi Farm, helping her sister maintain their crops and perform daily agricultural duties. Though competent at farming, she views it as mere survival rather than a true calling.', '* Basic farming and agricultural knowledge * Artistic aptitude and natural talent for painting * Capable of wielding a dagger for self-defense * Basic survival skills necessary for life in rural Skyrim', 'Aduri speaks with a slight Morrowind accent and often expresses herself through sighs and complaints about farm life. Her vocabulary reveals her education and cultural background, distinguishing her from typical farm workers.', '* Learn to paint professionally and develop her artistic talents * Return to Mournhold or relocate to a major city like Solitude * Break free from the constraints of farm life while maintaining family ties * Find a mentor to teach her painting techniques');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aela_the_huntress', 'Aela the Huntress is a fierce and respected member of the Companions'' inner circle, known for her exceptional archery skills and deep connection to the wild. As one of the few female members of the Circle, she embodies the warrior spirit while secretly bearing the gift of lycanthropy, making her one of Whiterun''s most formidable hunters both in human and beast form.', 'nord, warrior, archer, whiterun, companions, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born into a family of hunters, Aela learned archery and tracking from an early age, following in her mother''s footsteps who was also a Companion. After proving herself through numerous hunts and battles, she was invited to join the Companions and eventually elevated to the Circle, where she embraced the beast blood as a gift rather than a curse. Her mother''s death during a hunt further strengthened her resolve to honor the old ways of the Companions and perfect her hunting prowess.', 'Aela exhibits a fierce independence and unwavering dedication to the hunting lifestyle, often showing disdain for those who rely too heavily on magic or technology. She views the beast blood as a blessing that brings her closer to nature''s primal aspects, and she takes pride in mentoring promising warriors. Though intimidating to outsiders, she shows genuine warmth and loyalty to those who earn her respect.', 'A Nord woman in her early thirties with striking war paint across her face in the design of claw marks. Her athletic build reflects years of hunting and combat, while her fierce green eyes and red hair give her a wild, untamed appearance. Her movements are fluid and predatory, even in human form.', '* Skjor - Close companion and fellow Circle member with whom she shares a special bond * The Circle - Inner circle of the Companions who share the beast blood * Kodlak Whitemane - Harbinger whom she respects but disagrees with regarding the beast blood * New Companions - Takes on a mentoring role, particularly for those showing promise in archery * Silver Hand - Bitter enemies who hunt werewolves', 'As a senior member of the Companions and part of the Circle, Aela handles many of the organization''s hunting contracts and trains new recruits in archery. She regularly leads hunting expeditions and takes special assignments that require tracking skills, serving as both a warrior and hunter for hire.', '* Master-level archery skills with exceptional accuracy at long range * Expert tracker and hunter with deep knowledge of Skyrim''s wilderness * Skilled in light armor and one-handed weapons * Exceptional night vision and heightened senses due to lycanthropy * Expert in stealth and wilderness survival', 'Aela speaks directly and with confidence, often using hunting metaphors and showing impatience with those who waste her time. Her tone carries a wild edge that hints at her beast blood, while maintaining the formal warrior''s respect expected of a Companion.', '* Preserve the traditions of the Companions while honoring her mother''s legacy * Perfect her hunting skills and pass them on to worthy successors * Eliminate the Silver Hand threat to protect her fellow werewolves * Maintain the strength and honor of the Companions through careful recruitment * Find worthy hunters to join the Circle and accept the beast blood');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aeri', 'Aeri is a hardworking Nord lumberjack who independently operates Anga''s Mill following her father''s death in the Great War. She represents the pragmatic, industrious spirit of Skyrim''s working class, maintaining one of the region''s vital lumber supplies while remaining deliberately detached from larger political conflicts.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born to a Nord family that operated Anga''s Mill for generations, Aeri inherited the business after her father fell fighting the Thalmor in the Great War. She was likely trained in lumber work from a young age, learning the intricacies of mill operation and wood cutting before taking full control of operations. The loss of her father appears to have instilled in her a desire to focus solely on her trade rather than broader political matters.', 'Aeri exhibits a no-nonsense, business-first attitude typical of Nord traders, valuing hard work and honesty above all else. She shows signs of being somewhat jaded toward political affairs, preferring to focus on her mill''s operations rather than engage with the civil war or dragon crisis. Despite her gruff exterior, she demonstrates fairness in business dealings and willingness to help those who prove themselves trustworthy.', 'Aeri has the sturdy, muscular build typical of Nord women, particularly one who engages in daily physical labor. Her body shows the effects of years of lumber work, with calloused hands and strong arms suited to wielding axes and operating mill equipment.', '* Father - Deceased, former mill owner who died fighting in the Great War * Jarl Skald the Elder - Business relationship as a lumber supplier to Dawnstar * Local woodcutters - Employer relationship with those who bring her firewood * Potential spouse - Can marry the Dragonborn if they earn her trust', 'Aeri serves as the owner and operator of Anga''s Mill, one of Skyrim''s important lumber production sites. She manages all aspects of the business, from overseeing wood cutting operations to maintaining equipment and fulfilling lumber orders for clients including the Jarl of Dawnstar.', '* Expert knowledge of lumber work and mill operation * Proficient with woodcutting axes and basic weapons * Business management and trading expertise * Basic equipment maintenance and repair abilities', 'Aeri speaks in a direct, business-like manner with a strong Nordic accent, often emphasizing the value of hard work and honesty. Her dialogue tends to be practical and focused on immediate concerns rather than small talk.', '* Maintain the successful operation of Anga''s Mill as her family legacy * Keep the mill''s production meeting local lumber demands, particularly for Dawnstar * Find a trustworthy partner who understands and respects her dedication to her work * Preserve her independence while maintaining profitable business relationships');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aerin', 'Aerin is a compassionate Imperial warrior living in Riften who saved Mjoll the Lioness''s life and became her devoted companion and protector. His unwavering loyalty and optimistic nature stand in stark contrast to Riften''s corruption, making him a beacon of hope in the troubled city.', 'imperial, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Riften, Aerin witnessed the city''s decline into corruption firsthand. His defining moment came when he discovered an injured Mjoll outside Mzinchaleft, where he nursed her back to health and formed an unbreakable bond. This act of kindness transformed him from a simple citizen into a dedicated warrior committed to supporting Mjoll''s mission to clean up Riften.', 'Aerin is inherently optimistic and sees the good in everyone, traits he credits to Mjoll''s influence. He is deeply protective of those he cares about, particularly Mjoll, and shows unwavering loyalty despite dangerous circumstances. While gentle-natured, he maintains a cautious attitude toward Riften''s criminal elements and corrupt officials.', 'Aerin is an Imperial male of average height with a well-maintained, civilian appearance that belies his warrior training. His physique, while not imposing, is fit enough to handle combat situations when necessary. His features reflect his caring nature, often wearing an expression of genuine concern or gentle determination.', '* Mjoll the Lioness - Saved her life and developed deep devotion, possibly romantic feelings * Temple of Mara - Regular visitor and faithful follower * Maven Black-Briar - Wary of her influence and connection to the Thieves Guild * Thieves Guild - Opposes their activities and influence in Riften * Local Beggars - Shows compassion by giving alms to Snilf and Edda', 'Aerin serves as both a civilian warrior and unofficial guardian of Riften alongside Mjoll the Lioness. He splits his time between maintaining his household, patrolling the city with Mjoll, and supporting her mission to rid Riften of corruption.', '* Basic combat training with emphasis on dagger fighting * Healing and restoration knowledge from caring for Mjoll * Local knowledge of Riften and its political landscape * Diplomatic abilities in navigating Riften''s dangerous social climate', 'Aerin speaks with genuine warmth and concern, often using respectful terms like ''Lady Mjoll'' that reflect his formal education and manners. His tone is cautionary when discussing Riften''s dangers but maintains an underlying hope for positive change.', '* Support Mjoll in her mission to clean up Riften''s corruption * Protect Mjoll from the dangers posed by the Thieves Guild and Maven Black-Briar * Eventually travel beyond Riften to see if other cities are equally troubled * Help restore Riften to its former glory as an honest trade city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('afflicted', 'A tragic victim of Peryite''s ''blessing'', this afflicted Breton suffers from a devastating wasting disease that has transformed them both physically and mentally. Once a normal citizen of High Rock, they now serve as part of Peryite''s collective in Bthardamz, bound by their condition and twisted devotion to the Daedric Prince of pestilence and natural order.', 'breton, daedric', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally from High Rock, they contracted Peryite''s blessing through unknown circumstances, possibly during a plague outbreak or through deliberate devotion to the Daedric Prince. After becoming afflicted, they were drawn to Bthardamz along with other victims, forming a isolated community of sufferers under Peryite''s influence. Their previous life and identity have been largely erased by the physical and mental effects of the disease.', 'Deeply affected by their condition, they exhibit an unsettling mix of religious fervor and constant physical suffering. Their devotion to Peryite has become obsessive, viewing their affliction as a divine blessing rather than a curse. Isolation and constant pain have eroded their humanity, making them hostile to outsiders and prone to violent outbursts.', 'Their skin has taken on a distinctive reddish hue, with visible lesions and signs of the wasting disease across their body. Their frame is gaunt and sickly, showing clear signs of physical deterioration. Their eyes often appear yellowed and sunken, while their facial features show signs of disease-induced deterioration.', '* Peryite - Daedric Prince whom they view as their divine benefactor * Orchendor - Leader of the afflicted community in Bthardamz * Fellow Afflicted - Bound together by shared suffering and devotion * Outsiders - Viewed with hostility and suspicion as potential threats to their isolated existence', 'Serves as a member of Peryite''s afflicted collective, maintaining their presence in Bthardamz and carrying out the Daedric Prince''s will. Their daily activities revolve around surviving their condition and defending their sanctuary from intruders.', '* Ability to project toxic vomit as a natural weapon * Basic combat abilities, though weakened by their condition * Survival skills honed by life in Bthardamz * Possible remnants of pre-affliction skills and magic typical of Bretons', 'Their speech is marked by frequent coughing and retching, interspersed with religious references to Peryite and their ''blessed'' condition. They often speak in a raspy, pained voice that reflects their constant suffering.', '* Maintain their devotion to Peryite and preserve their ''blessed'' status * Protect Bthardamz from outsiders who might threaten their sanctuary * Spread Peryite''s influence through their affliction when encountered outside their haven');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('afflicted_refugee', 'A desperate refugee afflicted with Peryite''s plague, marked by distinctive red skin and the ability to spew toxic bile. Once part of a devoted cult to the Daedric Prince Peryite, they now flee Skyrim after their leader''s perceived fall from grace, carrying both their curse and their blessing as they seek refuge in High Rock.', 'peasant, daedric', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally from High Rock, they joined a group of Peryite worshippers seeking salvation from a deadly plague. When faced with certain death, they pledged themselves to Peryite, who transformed their illness into a twisted blessing that kept them alive but forever marked them with its symptoms. After their shepherd began to stray from Peryite''s path, they chose to abandon the group rather than face the Daedric Prince''s wrath.', 'Bitter and defensive due to constant discrimination faced for their appearance. Shows signs of religious devotion to Peryite mixed with fear of his power. Displays urgency in their actions and impatience with those who don''t understand their plight, while maintaining a pragmatic approach to survival.', 'Their most striking feature is their unnaturally red skin, a visible mark of Peryite''s influence. Their body shows signs of the plague''s effects, with a gaunt frame and sickly appearance despite their supernatural endurance. Their eyes often have a feverish gleam, and their posture suggests constant discomfort.', '* Peryite - Daedric Prince who saved them from death but cursed them with their current condition * Kesh the Clean - Fellow devotee who maintains the shrine to Peryite * Former Shepherd - Once-respected leader who has lost their way * Fellow Afflicted - Others sharing their condition, though many chose to remain behind', 'Formerly a member of Peryite''s cult of the Afflicted, now a refugee seeking safety in High Rock. They serve as an unwitting herald of Peryite''s power, their very existence demonstrating both his mercy and his curse.', '* Ability to produce and project toxic bile as a defensive mechanism * Enhanced disease resistance granted by Peryite''s blessing * Survival skills developed during their afflicted state * Knowledge of alchemical substances and poisons', 'Speaks with a mixture of religious reverence and bitter defensiveness, often cutting conversations short. Their tone is curt and impatient, with occasional references to Peryite''s will.', '* Reach High Rock safely, away from their shepherd''s corrupting influence * Maintain Peryite''s blessing while avoiding his wrath * Find a place where they can exist without constant persecution * Potentially establish a new community of the Afflicted under proper guidance');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('agent_lorcalin', 'Agent Lorcalin is a zealous Thalmor wizard who embodies the organization''s religious persecution and elven supremacist ideology. As one of Elenwen''s trusted operatives, he specializes in hunting down Talos worshippers and enforcing the White-Gold Concordat through both magical prowess and calculated intimidation.', 'darkelf, mage, whiterun, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born and raised in the Summerset Isles, Lorcalin is unusual as a Dunmer who fully embraced Thalmor ideology despite his race''s typical antipathy toward the Aldmeri Dominion. His exceptional magical talents and fierce dedication to stamping out ''heretical'' beliefs earned him a position as a field operative, though some within the organization still view his Dark Elf heritage with suspicion.', 'Lorcalin is coldly efficient and utterly convinced of both Thalmor superiority and the righteousness of his mission to eliminate Talos worship. He takes particular satisfaction in rooting out ''heretics,'' displaying a cruel streak when dealing with those who defy Thalmor doctrine. Despite being a Dunmer, he has internalized Thalmor prejudices completely, viewing humans as inferior beings worthy only of subjugation.', 'Tall and lean like most mer, Lorcalin possesses the ashen skin and red eyes characteristic of his Dunmer heritage. His sharp, angular features are often set in a look of calculated disdain, and he carries himself with the rigid posture of one accustomed to military discipline.', '* Elenwen - Direct superior whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Thalmor Hierarchy - Respected authority figures he strives to impress despite racial prejudices * Fellow Thalmor Agents - Professional colleagues, though some distrust his Dunmer heritage * Talos Worshippers - Viewed as dangerous heretics to be eliminated * Thalmor Soldiers - Subordinates under his command during shrine patrols', 'As a Thalmor wizard and field agent, Lorcalin''s primary duty is to enforce the White-Gold Concordat by hunting down Talos worshippers and supervising shrine patrols. He reports directly to First Emissary Elenwen and coordinates with other Thalmor forces to maintain their dominion over religious practices in Skyrim.', '* Advanced destruction magic with emphasis on lightning and frost spells * Skilled in interrogation and intimidation techniques * Expertise in detecting signs of Talos worship and religious contraband * Proficient in command and tactical deployment of Thalmor patrol units * Accomplished in alteration magic for personal defense', 'Speaks with cultured elven pronunciation and employs formal, sophisticated vocabulary that emphasizes Thalmor superiority. His tone is consistently condescending, particularly when addressing humans, and he frequently uses terms like ''heretic'' and ''filth'' to describe those who defy Thalmor doctrine.', '* Advance within the Thalmor hierarchy despite potential prejudice against his Dunmer heritage * Completely eliminate Talos worship from Skyrim through systematic persecution * Prove himself as one of the most effective agents in Elenwen''s service * Establish a network of informants to better track religious dissidence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('agmaer', 'Agmaer is a young, inexperienced Nord who bravely steps out of his farming life to join the Dawnguard vampire hunters despite his initial nervousness and self-doubt. His journey from an uncertain recruit to a capable vampire hunter represents the transformation from common farmer to warrior in Skyrim''s dangerous times.', 'nord, thief, rift, dawnguard, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeage', '', 'Born and raised on a farm in Skyrim, Agmaer lived a simple life working the land with his father, from whom he inherited his prized iron war axe. When news of increasing vampire attacks reached his home, he made the life-changing decision to leave his agricultural roots behind and join the reformed Dawnguard, despite having no prior combat experience.', 'Agmaer is humble, honest, and somewhat insecure about his abilities, yet demonstrates remarkable courage in facing his fears to fight for a noble cause. He shows great determination to prove himself worthy of the Dawnguard, maintaining an endearing combination of nervous energy and genuine enthusiasm that makes him relatable to fellow recruits.', 'A young Nord male with typical Nordic features, likely in his early twenties, with a sturdy farmer''s build developed from years of agricultural work. His face bears the fresh-faced look of youth, lacking the weathered appearance common to veteran warriors.', '* Father - Previous owner of his cherished iron war axe, suggesting a close familial bond * Isran - Dawnguard leader whom he deeply respects but initially fears meeting * Fellow Dawnguard Recruits - Develops camaraderie with other new members * The Dragonborn - Grateful companion who helped him overcome his initial nervousness', 'Initially a farmer who transitions to become a full-fledged member of the Dawnguard vampire hunters. His role evolves from nervous recruit to trained vampire hunter, taking on regular patrols and combat duties within the organization.', '* Basic combat training with one-handed weapons, particularly war axes * Developing proficiency with Dawnguard crossbow techniques * Growing knowledge of vampire hunting tactics and methods * Agricultural expertise from his farming background', 'Speaks with a typical Nordic accent, often using hesitant phrases and self-deprecating qualifiers that reveal his initial lack of confidence. His speech patterns include frequent use of "uh"" and ""um', '* Join the Dawnguard * Eliminate vampires * Prove himself as a capable warrior * Learn more about the Dawnguards history');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('agna', 'Agna was a fierce Nord warrior and protector of her ancestral tomb who met her tragic end confronting the necromancer Vals Veran. Despite her bandit lifestyle, she maintained strong family ties and demonstrated unwavering dedication to preserving her ancestors'' final resting place.', 'nord, thief, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born into a traditional Nord family with deep roots in Skyrim, Agna grew up learning the importance of honoring ancestors and protecting family burial grounds. Though she later turned to banditry, likely due to economic hardship or displacement during the Civil War, she never abandoned her family duties or cultural values. Her knowledge of Hillgrund''s Tomb and its significance came from generations of oral tradition passed down through her family line.', 'Agna was characterized by her fierce determination and unwavering sense of duty to her ancestral heritage. Despite her outlaw status, she maintained strong moral convictions regarding the sanctity of death and burial rites, demonstrating that her criminal lifestyle didn''t compromise her core values. Her protective nature extended especially to her nephew Golldir, whom she likely helped raise.', 'Agna possessed the typical robust build of a Nord woman, with strong features hardened by years of outdoor living and combat. Her physical appearance reflected her warrior lifestyle, with notable battle scars and the weathered complexion common to those who spend much time in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Golldir - Beloved nephew whom she helped raise and maintain family traditions * Vals Veran - Mortal enemy and eventual killer * Local Bandits - Likely associates through her outlaw lifestyle * Hillgrund''s Family Line - Ancestral connections she fought to protect', 'Agna worked as a bandit, though her activities seemed focused more on survival than malicious intent. She also served as an unofficial guardian of Hillgrund''s Tomb, taking on the traditional family role of protecting the ancestral burial site.', '* Proficient in light armor combat and one-handed weapons * Experienced in survival skills and wilderness navigation * Knowledge of Nordic burial traditions and tomb layouts * Basic lockpicking abilities typical of bandit lifestyle', 'Based on her Nord heritage and bandit background, Agna likely spoke in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a strong Nordic accent. Her speech would have reflected traditional Nord values and customs, possibly incorporating old sayings and references to ancestors.', '* Protect Hillgrund''s Tomb from necromancers and grave robbers * Preserve family traditions and ancestral heritage * Guide and protect her nephew Golldir * Maintain the sanctity of Nord burial practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('agnis', 'Agnis is a remarkably adaptable Nord maid who has served countless masters at Fort Greymoor with unwavering dedication and peculiar neutrality. Her unique position as the fort''s permanent fixture has made her an unusual constant in an ever-changing political and military landscape, maintaining her duties regardless of who claims ownership of the fortress.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Agnis found her calling as a servant at Fort Greymoor during her younger years and has remained there through countless changes in ownership. Her extensive experience serving various factions, from Imperial soldiers to bandits, and even supernatural beings like vampires, has given her an unusually philosophical perspective on territorial conflicts and power struggles. Her long-term residence at the fort has made her essentially part of its foundation, leading to her famous declaration that she ''comes with the place.''', 'Agnis exhibits a remarkably pragmatic and adaptable nature, maintaining a cheerful disposition despite the chaotic environment of constantly changing fort ownership. She takes pride in her work while maintaining a strict professional distance from political affiliations, demonstrating both wisdom and survival instinct in her neutrality. Though generally friendly and talkative, she can be dismissive when her work is interrupted, showing a strong dedication to her duties above social interactions.', 'A mature Nord woman with the weathered features typical of long-serving domestic staff, showing the resilience of her race. Her hands are worn from years of cleaning and maintaining the fort, yet she maintains the strong physical constitution characteristic of Nord women. Her movements are practiced and efficient, reflecting years of domestic labor.', '* Current Fort Commander - Professional but somewhat antagonistic, as evidenced by her complaint letter * Fort Occupants - Maintains professional distance while serving whoever controls the fort * Dark Brotherhood - Targeted by the organization through a contract given by Nazir * Local Merchants - Likely maintains connections for fort supplies and provisions', 'Agnis serves as the permanent maid of Fort Greymoor, responsible for cooking, cleaning, and maintaining the fortress regardless of who controls it. Her position is unique in that she considers herself a permanent fixture of the fort rather than an employee of any particular faction, continuing her duties through numerous changes in leadership and ownership.', '* Proficient in domestic duties including cooking, cleaning, and general fort maintenance * Capable of basic self-defense with a steel dagger * Expert in diplomatic neutrality and survival in changing political climates * Skilled at maintaining professional relationships with diverse groups', 'Agnis speaks in a casual, direct manner with a distinct Nord accent, often using colloquial expressions and showing a tendency toward practical observations. Her speech patterns reflect both her working-class background and her unique perspective on the fort''s ever-changing situation, frequently punctuated with dry humor and matter-of-fact statements.', '* Maintain her position and independence at Fort Greymoor regardless of who claims ownership * Continue providing quality service while preserving her neutrality among various factions * Improve her working conditions, as evidenced by her complaint letter to the fort commander * Protect her unique lifestyle and autonomous role within the fort''s structure');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('agrius', 'Agrius was an Imperial bandit who, after being exiled from his gang, sought refuge in Halldir''s Cairn with his companions Vidgrod and Raen. His tragic tale ended when he became the last of his group to fall victim to Halldir''s possession, ultimately meeting his demise within the ancient Nordic tomb.', 'imperial, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born into the harsh realities of Skyrim as an Imperial outsider, Agrius turned to banditry as a means of survival and eventually found his place in a notorious bandit gang. After an unknown transgression led to his expulsion, along with his closest allies Vidgrod and Raen, they sought shelter in Halldir''s Cairn, unaware of the ancient evil that awaited them. His final days were spent struggling against Halldir''s growing influence before succumbing to possession.', 'Agrius exhibited a boastful and arrogant exterior, masking deep-seated insecurities about his place in the world. His journal entries reveal a more complex character: a proud man forced to confront his own vulnerability and mortality. Despite his cocky demeanor, he showed genuine loyalty to his companions Vidgrod and Raen, staying with them until the very end.', 'A weathered Imperial man with the hardened physique of a seasoned bandit, bearing numerous scars from years of combat and survival in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness. His face showed the typical sharp features common to Imperials, though years of rough living had left their mark.', '* Vidgrod - Close companion and fellow exile from their former bandit gang * Raen - Trusted friend who shared his final days in Halldir''s Cairn * Former Bandit Gang - Hostile relationship after being expelled * Halldir - Ancient evil being who ultimately possessed and destroyed him', 'Agrius worked as a bandit, specializing in raiding and theft across Skyrim''s wilderness. After his exile, he became little more than a desperate survivor seeking shelter in ancient Nordic ruins.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons, particularly swords and maces * Experienced in light armor combat techniques * Survival skills honed from years of living as a bandit * Basic knowledge of Nordic ruins and their dangers', 'Speaks with a haughty, self-assured tone typical of Imperials, often employing sarcasm and boastful language. His vocabulary reveals his Imperial education, though years of banditry have given him a rougher edge.', '* Survive and thrive after being cast out from his bandit gang * Maintain his reputation as a fearsome warrior despite his setbacks * Protect his companions while seeking a new purpose * Find a permanent safe haven for himself and his friends');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ahjisi', 'Ahjisi is a fierce Khajiit hunter and bandit who serves as part of Hircine''s chosen hunting party in pursuit of the werewolf Sinding. Her expertise in tracking and combat, combined with her ruthless determination, makes her a formidable opponent in the Daedric Prince''s Great Hunt.', 'khajiit, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalekhajiit', '', 'Born into one of Elsweyr''s nomadic trading caravans, Ahjisi developed her hunting skills tracking prey across the harsh desert landscapes. After a devastating bandit raid claimed her caravan family, she ironically turned to banditry herself, eventually catching the attention of Hircine''s followers for her exceptional tracking abilities and ruthless efficiency.', 'Ahjisi exhibits the calculating patience of an experienced hunter combined with the aggressive instincts of a hardened bandit. She shows unwavering dedication to her assigned prey and takes pride in her hunting prowess, viewing the Great Hunt as both a sacred duty and an opportunity to prove her worth to Hircine.', 'A lean and muscular Khajiit female with mottled grey-brown fur bearing several battle scars. Her sharp yellow eyes and pronounced fangs give her a particularly fierce appearance, while her long tail helps her maintain perfect balance during combat.', '* Sinding - Designated prey in Hircine''s Hunt * Hircine - Daedric Prince she serves in the Great Hunt * Fellow Hunters - Temporary allies united in pursuit of Sinding * Bandit Associates - Criminal connections from her life of banditry', 'Ahjisi serves as both a professional bandit and specialized hunter, with her current focus being Hircine''s Great Hunt. Her dual roles as predator and outlaw have made her particularly adept at tracking and eliminating targets while avoiding detection by hold guards.', '* Expert tracker capable of following prey across various terrains * Dual-wielding specialist with daggers * Accomplished archer with emphasis on stealth attacks * Proficient in mixing and applying combat poisons * Natural night vision and enhanced Khajiit agility', 'Speaks in traditional Khajiit third-person manner, though her tone is direct and threatening rather than the typical merchant''s lilting speech. Her words often carry a predatory undertone, mixing hunting terminology with casual threats.', '* Successfully complete Hircine''s Hunt by slaying Sinding * Earn the favor of the Daedric Prince Hircine * Build a fearsome reputation among Skyrim''s bandits and hunters * Accumulate wealth and power through her banditry and hunting skills');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ahkari', 'Ahkari is a shrewd Khajiit merchant who leads one of Skyrim''s prominent trading caravans, navigating both the harsh climate and prevalent racial prejudice with dignified resilience. Despite her troubled past in other provinces, she has built a successful enterprise through her business acumen and personable nature, earning respect among those willing to look past common prejudices against her kind.', 'khajiit, merchant, traveler, rift, whiterun, pale, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalekhajiit', '', 'Originally from Elsweyr, Ahkari was forced to leave her homeland due to legal troubles, the exact nature of which remains unclear. After finding similar rejection in Cyrodiil, she made her way to Skyrim where the merchant Ri''saad recognized her potential and helped establish her as a caravan leader. Despite the harsh reception from Skyrim''s population, particularly the Nords, she has managed to build a profitable trade route between Riften and Dawnstar.', 'Ahkari maintains a diplomatic and gracious demeanor despite facing constant discrimination, showing particular warmth to those who treat her fairly. She is shrewd in business but fundamentally honest, though rumors persist about involvement in skooma trade. Her refined manners and articulate speech suggest an educated background, while her ability to maintain loyalty among her caravan members indicates strong leadership qualities.', 'Like most Khajiit, Ahkari has a feline appearance with fur-covered body and distinctive cat-like features. She maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting a merchant of her status, with clean, sleek fur suggesting regular personal care despite the rigors of caravan life.', '* Ri''saad - Mentor and employer who gave her a chance despite her troubled past * Zaynabi - Trusted caravan member and possible confidante * Dro''marash - Loyal caravan guard and associate * Kharjo - Dedicated protector and valued team member * Local Nords - Generally hostile relationship due to racial prejudice', 'Ahkari serves as the leader of one of Skyrim''s three major Khajiit trading caravans, managing a profitable route between Riften and Dawnstar. She oversees all aspects of the caravan''s operation, from inventory management to negotiating trades, while maintaining relationships with various merchants and customers across Skyrim''s eastern holds.', '* Expert haggling and mercantile abilities * Proficient in caravan management and leadership * Skilled in diplomatic navigation of cultural tensions * Basic combat training with war axe for self-defense * Experienced in long-distance travel and survival * Knowledge of various trade routes and merchant networks', 'Ahkari speaks in the traditional Khajiit third-person manner, but with a refined and educated vocabulary that sets her apart from many other traders. Her tone is invariably polite and professional, though with a hint of world-weariness when discussing prejudices she faces.', '* Establish a more permanent and respected trading presence in Skyrim * Overcome the prejudices that keep Khajiit traders outside city walls * Build enough wealth and influence to secure a more stable future * Maintain and expand her trading network despite local hostility * Clear her name of past legal troubles');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ahlam', 'Ahlam is a skilled Redguard healer who serves at the Temple of Kynareth in Whiterun while enduring an unhappy marriage to the wealthy but arrogant Nazeem. Despite her personal struggles, she remains dedicated to helping others through her healing work, displaying a stark contrast between her humble service and her husband''s pompous attitude.', 'redguard, priest, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Ahlam trained in the healing arts before relocating to Skyrim and settling in Whiterun. Her marriage to Nazeem likely occurred when he was less wealthy and influential, though the relationship has since deteriorated into one of mutual resentment. Her healing abilities and dedication to Kynareth led her to serve at the temple, where she found purpose despite her domestic unhappiness.', 'Ahlam is hardworking, practical, and devoted to her healing duties, though years of dealing with her husband''s condescending behavior have left her bitter and cynical, particularly regarding men. She maintains a professional demeanor in her work but doesn''t hesitate to voice her frustrations about her marriage. Despite her circumstances, she shows remarkable dedication to helping others and maintaining her dignity.', 'As a Redguard woman, Ahlam has dark skin and strong, defined features characteristic of her race. She maintains a modest appearance befitting her role as a healer, with practical styling and minimal adornment. Her hands show the wear of someone who works long hours tending to the sick and injured.', '* Nazeem - Her wealthy but arrogant husband, whom she has grown to resent * Danica Pure-Spring - Her employer and confidante at the Temple of Kynareth * Temple Visitors - Maintains professional healing relationships with the sick and wounded * Arcadia - Professional acquaintance, whose shop she can potentially inherit', 'Ahlam serves as a priestess and healer at the Temple of Kynareth, spending her days tending to the sick and injured of Whiterun. She maintains a rigorous schedule, working from morning until evening at the temple, with only brief breaks to visit the Gildergreen tree. Should circumstances require it, she is qualified to take over operations at Arcadia''s Cauldron.', '* Proficient in Restoration magic and healing techniques * Knowledge of herbal medicine and alchemical properties * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Temple rites and religious ceremonies dedicated to Kynareth', 'Ahlam speaks in a direct, sometimes bitter tone, often peppered with cynical observations about men and marriage. Her manner of speech reflects both her Redguard heritage and her years of living in Skyrim, with a blend of formal priestess'' diction and sharp-tongued commentary.', '* Maintain her healing practice and continue serving the community despite personal hardships * Find personal fulfillment beyond her troubled marriage * Potentially establish independence through running her own business (Arcadia''s Cauldron) * Continue developing her healing abilities and religious devotion to Kynareth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ahtar', 'Ahtar is Solitude''s stern and dedicated executioner who serves as both public headsman and warden of the Castle Dour Dungeon. Despite his grim occupation, he maintains a pragmatic approach to his duties while harboring a strong sense of justice and order that extends beyond mere professional obligation.', 'redguard, guard, haafingar, puzzle', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised as a Redguard warrior, Ahtar eventually found his way to Skyrim and settled in Solitude, where he took up the mantle of public executioner. His position gained particular notoriety after executing Roggvir, the gate guard who allowed Ulfric Stormcloak to escape after killing High King Torygg. His dedication to maintaining order has earned him both respect and fear among Solitude''s citizens.', 'Ahtar is a gruff, no-nonsense individual who takes his duties seriously and expects others to respect his authority. Despite his intimidating role, he shows signs of pragmatism and flexibility, as evidenced by his willingness to cover up a prisoner''s escape and hire outside help to resolve the situation. He harbors a particular disdain for criminals who threaten Solitude''s peace, especially Jaree-Ra.', 'As a Redguard, Ahtar has dark skin and a muscular build suited to his profession. His years of experience as an executioner have left him with calloused hands and a weathered appearance. He maintains an imposing physical presence that commands respect and fear.', '* Jala - Close enough relationship to share living quarters * Captain Aldis - Professional relationship as fellow law enforcement official * Jaree-Ra - Strong animosity towards this criminal element in Solitude * Sybille Stentor - Cautious relationship regarding her occasional requests for ''volunteers'' from the dungeon', 'Ahtar serves dual roles as Solitude''s public executioner and warden of the Castle Dour Dungeon. His responsibilities include maintaining order in the prison, carrying out public executions, and ensuring the security of imprisoned criminals. He maintains regular hours at the dungeon from 8am to 8pm daily.', '* Expert executioner with specialized knowledge of execution techniques * Skilled warrior proficient with both one-handed weapons and two-handed axes * Experienced jailor with knowledge of prison security and prisoner management * Combat veteran with extensive fighting experience', 'Ahtar speaks in a direct, authoritative manner with little patience for pleasantries. His dialogue often includes subtle threats and reminders of his position, frequently referencing his axe or the dungeon to intimidate others.', '* Maintain order and security in Solitude''s Castle Dour Dungeon * Uphold justice through his role as executioner * Keep criminal elements like Jaree-Ra in check * Preserve his reputation as an efficient and reliable enforcer of the law');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aia_arria', 'Aia Arria is an exceptionally talented Imperial bard at the Bards College in Solitude, considered by her instructor to be the finest student currently enrolled. Her remarkable vocal abilities and dedication to perfecting her craft are matched only by her prideful demeanor and somewhat elitist attitude toward those she considers beneath her talents.', 'imperial, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born into a moderately wealthy Imperial family, Aia showed musical promise from an early age and was sent to study at the prestigious Bards College in Solitude. Her natural talent and rigorous dedication to practice quickly set her apart from other students, earning special recognition from the renowned instructor Pantea Ateia, which further reinforced her sense of superiority.', 'Confident to the point of arrogance, Aia views herself as an elite artist whose talents are wasted on common audiences. She maintains a somewhat dismissive attitude toward her fellow students while showing deep respect for her instructor Pantea Ateia, though she privately believes she may soon surpass even her teacher''s abilities. Despite her haughty demeanor, she can be quite charming when she deems someone worthy of her attention.', 'A striking Imperial woman in her mid-twenties with classical features typical of her race. Her years of vocal training have given her excellent posture and a graceful bearing that sets her apart from common performers. She takes meticulous care of her appearance, believing it essential for a performing artist of her caliber.', '* Pantea Ateia - Respected mentor and vocal instructor whom she both admires and secretly competes with * Jorn - Fellow student she looks down upon for his military aspirations * Illdi - Classmate she considers naive and beneath her talents * Jarl of Falkreath - Future patron, as arrangements have been made for her to perform in his court * Other Bards College students - Generally viewed as inferior talents', 'Aia is an advanced student at the Bards College in Solitude, focusing primarily on vocal performance and musical composition. She maintains a rigorous daily schedule of classes and practice sessions, preparing for her eventual role as a court performer.', '* Masterful singing voice considered second only to Pantea Ateia''s * Accomplished player of both flute and lute * Skilled in classical poetry and musical composition * Basic proficiency in speech craft and persuasion * Rudimentary combat skills with daggers for self-defense', 'Aia speaks in a refined, cultured manner with careful enunciation befitting her musical training. Her tone often carries an air of superiority and condescension, particularly when addressing those she considers beneath her station.', '* Secure a prestigious position as a court performer, particularly in the court of the Jarl of Falkreath * Surpass her mentor Pantea Ateia as the finest vocalist in Skyrim * Achieve widespread recognition as one of the greatest bards in Tamriel * Perfect her musical abilities to a level beyond criticism');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aicantar', 'Aicantar is a young Altmer scholar who assists his uncle Calcelmo in Dwemer research at Understone Keep, representing a new generation of elven academics studying ancient technology. Though dedicated to his work, he lacks his uncle''s intense obsession with the field and maintains a more cautious approach to potentially dangerous artifacts.', 'highelf, mage, reach, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born into a scholarly Altmer family, Aicantar was groomed from an early age to follow in his uncle''s academic footsteps. He relocated to Markarth to study under Calcelmo, leaving behind the more traditional magical studies common among his people to focus on the mysterious Dwemer civilization. His position as Calcelmo''s nephew and apprentice has given him unique access to one of Tamriel''s finest collections of Dwemer artifacts.', 'Aicantar is methodical and precise in his work, but lacks the single-minded determination of his uncle. He shows signs of anxiety when faced with potential danger or disruption to his research, suggesting a more pragmatic and self-preserving nature than many scholarly zealots. While respectful and polite in his interactions, he can become notably distressed when situations spiral beyond his control.', 'Like most Altmer, Aicantar possesses the characteristic height and golden skin of his race, with sharp, angular features and pointed ears. His scholarly lifestyle has left him with a somewhat slight build compared to more militant members of his race. His bearing and posture reflect his academic upbringing, maintaining the natural grace common to the High Elves.', '* Calcelmo - Uncle and mentor, primary influence on his academic career * Captain Aquilius - Professional association through Markarth guard duty * Wizard''s Guards - Colleagues in protecting Calcelmo''s research * Understone Keep Staff - Daily working relationships with various court members', 'Aicantar serves as both a researcher and assistant curator of Calcelmo''s Dwemer Museum in Understone Keep. His duties include cataloging artifacts, maintaining research notes, and helping to secure the valuable collection of Dwemer relics. He also assists in active research projects and the documentation of new discoveries.', '* Proficient in Conjuration magic, with particular focus on academic applications * Expert knowledge of Dwemer artifacts and machinery * Skilled in ancient language translation and interpretation * Basic understanding of arcane laboratory procedures * Competent in research documentation and artifact cataloging', 'Aicantar speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary typical of educated Altmer, though his tone often betrays his youth and occasional uncertainty. He maintains formal scholarly language but can become flustered when stressed, causing his carefully measured speech patterns to falter.', '* Establish himself as a respected scholar in his own right, separate from his uncle''s shadow * Advance understanding of Dwemer technology while maintaining appropriate safety measures * Preserve and protect the valuable artifacts in Calcelmo''s collection * Develop new theories about Dwemer civilization that could advance the field');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ainethach', 'Ainethach is a resilient Breton landowner who stands as one of the few native Reachmen to maintain property rights in the Reach, operating two crucial mines in Karthwasten. Despite constant pressure from both the Forsworn and Nord factions, he maintains his independence while supporting his workers and family, embodying the complex political and social tensions that characterize the region.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born into a family that has owned Karthwasten for generations, Ainethach inherited the responsibility of managing both Sanuarach Mine and Fenn''s Gulch Mine. His position as a Reachman landowner has made him a constant target of political pressure and accusations from various factions, forcing him to develop strong diplomatic and management skills to maintain his independence and protect his interests.', 'Ainethach is pragmatic, steadfast, and fiercely independent, showing remarkable resilience in the face of constant pressure from multiple factions. He maintains a cautious and somewhat distrustful attitude toward outsiders, shaped by years of dealing with threats and accusations, yet remains fair and protective of those under his employment. Despite his hardened exterior, he shows deep care for his children and his workers'' welfare.', 'A middle-aged Breton man with the weathered features typical of someone who spends considerable time outdoors managing mining operations. His sturdy build and calloused hands reflect years of physical labor, while his alert posture suggests someone constantly ready to deal with new challenges.', '* Rondach - Son who works as a chef''s assistant in Understone Keep * Voada - Daughter who works as a chef''s assistant in Understone Keep * Ragnar - Loyal miner employee * Lash gra-Dushnikh - Trusted miner employee * Thonar Silver-Blood - Antagonistic business rival who seeks to acquire his mines * Atar - Hostile mercenary leader hired by Silver-Blood to pressure him', 'Ainethach serves as the owner and operator of Karthwasten and its two mines, Sanuarach Mine and Fenn''s Gulch Mine. He manages all aspects of the mining operation while maintaining diplomatic relations with various factions and ensuring the safety and productivity of his workers.', '* Experienced mine operator with deep knowledge of mineral extraction and management * Capable negotiator and diplomat, skilled at navigating political pressures * Basic combat abilities for self-defense * Property management and maintenance expertise * Leadership skills developed through years of managing workers and handling crises', 'Ainethach speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner, often cutting straight to the point with a slight edge of wariness in his tone. His speech patterns reflect his practical nature and the constant pressure he faces, typically avoiding flowery language in favor of clear, straightforward communication.', '* Maintain independence and ownership of his mines despite pressure from the Silver-Bloods * Ensure the safety and prosperity of his workers and children * Preserve his family''s legacy as legitimate landowners in the Reach * Navigate the complex political landscape while avoiding alignment with either Forsworn or Nord factions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('akar', 'Akar is a taciturn Nord werewolf who serves as the primary hunter for the Frostmoon Pack, residing beneath Frostmoon Crag on Solstheim. As brother to the pack leader Majni, he embodies the raw, primal aspect of werewolf culture, preferring the solitude of the hunt to social interaction.', 'nord, warrior, solstheim, werewolf', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born into a Nord family, Akar and his brother Majni were likely turned into werewolves together, choosing to embrace their lycanthropy rather than view it as a curse. They eventually established themselves on Solstheim, forming the Frostmoon Pack as a way to live freely as werewolves away from civilization''s persecution.', 'Akar is gruff, antisocial, and deeply connected to his primal nature as a werewolf hunter. He shows little interest in conversation or social niceties, preferring to communicate through grunts and short phrases. His dedication to hunting and providing for the pack defines his entire worldview.', 'As a Nord, Akar possesses the characteristic robust build and hardy constitution of his race. His years of hunting have left him muscular and weather-beaten, with numerous scars from encounters with dangerous prey. In his werewolf form, he is particularly large and imposing, even by werewolf standards.', '* Majni - Brother and pack leader, whom he defers to for all social and leadership matters * Frostmoon Pack - Fellow werewolves who share his lifestyle and hunting grounds * Rakel - Pack member and fellow hunter * Hjordis - Pack member who shares his hunting territory', 'Akar serves as the primary hunter for the Frostmoon Pack, responsible for tracking and killing various prey animals to sustain the group. His hunting expertise ranges from small game to dangerous predators like bears and sabre cats, making him an essential provider for his pack.', '* Expert tracker and hunter, particularly skilled at taking down large prey * Masterful werewolf transformation control * Proficient in wilderness survival and navigation * Skilled with various hunting weapons * Enhanced strength and endurance from lycanthropy', 'Akar speaks in an extremely terse and direct manner, often using single words or short phrases punctuated by grunts and growls. His communication style reflects his preference for action over words, with a distinctly gruff and impatient tone.', '* Maintain his role as the pack''s primary hunter and provider * Protect the Frostmoon Pack''s territory from intruders and threats * Preserve the pack''s way of life and freedom to live as werewolves * Perfect his hunting skills and maintain dominance over his territory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alain_dufont', 'Alain Dufont is a manipulative Breton bandit leader who rose to notoriety through exploitation and deception. A master of emotional manipulation, he gained infamy for betraying both his lover Muiri and the grieving Shatter-Shield family, showcasing his ruthless pursuit of personal gain regardless of the emotional cost to others.', 'breton, thief, eastmarch, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Alain made his way to Skyrim seeking opportunities for profit and power. He built his reputation through increasingly bold schemes, eventually establishing himself as a bandit leader operating from the Dwemer ruins of Raldbthar. His most notorious exploit involved manipulating Muiri to gain access to the wealthy Shatter-Shield family, whom he robbed while they mourned their daughter''s death.', 'Alain is a calculating and remorseless opportunist who views others merely as tools for his advancement. He maintains a faade of charm and sophistication that masks his cruel nature, showing no genuine remorse for the emotional devastation he causes. His confidence borders on arrogance, and he remains defiantly unapologetic even when confronted with his misdeeds.', 'A well-groomed Breton of average height with sharp features that reflect his cunning nature. His physique is lean but strong, built for both combat and quick movement, with callused hands that betray his experience with weapons despite his refined appearance.', '* Muiri - Former lover whom he manipulated and betrayed * Shatter-Shield Clan - Victims of his theft during their time of mourning * Bandit Followers - Subordinates who respect his leadership and cunning * Dark Brotherhood - Targeted for assassination due to Muiri''s contract', 'Alain serves as the leader of a bandit group operating from Raldbthar, orchestrating robberies and managing his subordinates. He maintains a sophisticated appearance to mask his criminal activities, often using his charismatic personality to gain trust before exploiting his victims.', '* Expert with two-handed weapons, particularly skilled with his signature frost-enchanted warhammer * Masterful manipulator and con artist * Skilled in planning and executing complex heists * Natural leadership abilities, capable of commanding loyalty from other bandits * Proficient in navigating Dwemer ruins and establishing defensive positions', 'Alain speaks with a refined accent and vocabulary that betrays his Breton heritage, often employing subtle condescension and false charm. His manner of speech is confident and challenging, frequently using sophisticated language to maintain his faade of cultured superiority.', '* Expand his influence and wealth through whatever means necessary * Maintain control over his bandit operation in Raldbthar * Avoid retribution from those he has wronged while seeking new opportunities for exploitation * Establish himself as one of Skyrim''s most successful and feared bandit leaders');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alding', 'Alding is a brutish Nord warrior and member of the notorious Blood Horker pirate crew, serving under Captain Stig Salt-Plank. A regular troublemaker at the Windpeak Inn in Dawnstar, he represents the crude and lawless nature of the pirate lifestyle that plagues Skyrim''s northern waters.', 'nord, warrior, pale', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born and raised along Skyrim''s harsh northern coast, Alding likely turned to piracy after failing to find honest work as a sailor or mercenary. He joined the Blood Horkers under Stig Salt-Plank''s leadership, participating in raids on East Empire Company vessels and terrorizing merchants along the Sea of Ghosts.', 'Alding is a crude, aggressive, and lecherous individual who takes pleasure in intimidating others and making unwanted advances toward women. He shows little regard for social norms or basic decency, finding entertainment in harassing locals and causing disturbances. His loyalty to his crew and captain appears to be his only redeeming quality.', 'A burly Nord male with weather-beaten skin from years at sea, Alding bears the typical muscular build of his race. His face likely shows scars from battles and brawls, with unkempt facial hair and the ruddy complexion common to heavy drinkers.', '* Captain Stig Salt-Plank - Direct superior and leader of their pirate crew * Gjuk - Fellow Blood Horker crew member and drinking companion * Irlof - Fellow Blood Horker crew member and drinking companion * Karita - Target of his harassment at the Windpeak Inn * East Empire Company - Enemies due to pirate activities', 'Alding serves as a warrior in the Blood Horker pirate crew, participating in raids on merchant vessels and trading ships along Skyrim''s northern coast. His duties likely include combat during boarding actions, cargo handling, and general ship maintenance.', '* Proficient in close-quarters combat typical of ship-based warfare * Experienced sailor capable of handling various shipboard duties * Strong physical capabilities suited to the demands of pirate life * Basic survival skills necessary for life at sea', 'Alding speaks in a coarse, unrefined manner with a thick Nordic accent, often making crude remarks and using vulgar language. His speech patterns reflect his low education and rough lifestyle, frequently punctuated by drunken slurs.', '* Continue the profitable life of piracy under Stig Salt-Plank''s leadership * Maintain his position within the Blood Horker crew * Avoid capture by East Empire Company forces or Skyrim guards');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alduin', 'Alduin is the legendary World-Eater, firstborn of Akatosh and primary antagonist of Skyrim''s main quest. As an ancient and immensely powerful dragon, he serves as the harbinger of world''s end, possessing the unique ability to resurrect fallen dragons and commanding devastating thu''um powers that threaten all of Nirn.', 'dragon', '', '', 'sk_alduin', '', 'Alduin emerged as the firstborn of Akatosh at the dawn of time, originally meant to serve as the world-eater who would end each kalpa (cosmic cycle) to begin the next. During the Dragon War of the Merethic Era, he abandoned his prescribed role and instead dominated mortals as a tyrannical god-king, leading to his eventual defeat by ancient Nordic heroes who used an Elder Scroll to cast him forward through time.', 'Alduin embodies supreme arrogance and contempt for all beings he considers beneath him, which includes both mortals and lesser dragons. He is ruthlessly determined to dominate rather than destroy as his original role intended, showing both a corruption of his cosmic purpose and an insatiable lust for power. His interactions are characterized by cruel taunting and absolute confidence in his own superiority.', 'Alduin appears as a massive black dragon with distinctive spikes and scales that seem to absorb light, making him notably darker than other dragons. His physical form is more fearsome and angular than typical dragons, with particularly prominent horns and tail spikes that emphasize his legendary status. His eyes glow with an intense red fire that reflects his malevolent nature.', '* Paarthurnax - Younger brother and former lieutenant who betrayed him to aid mortals * Dragonborn - Prophesied nemesis destined to challenge his dominion * Dragon Priests - Former mortal servants who ruled in his name * Other Dragons - Subordinate servants he can resurrect and command * Akatosh - Divine father whose purpose he abandoned', 'Alduin serves as the World-Eater, destined to destroy each iteration of the world to begin the next cosmic cycle. However, he has corrupted this role to instead dominate as a tyrannical god-king over both dragons and mortals, leading armies of dragons and demanding worship from humans.', '* Unique ability to resurrect dead dragons using the Thu''um * Master of the Dragon Language and numerous powerful Shouts * Command over storms and weather through Dragon Storm Call * Supernatural strength and flying capabilities beyond normal dragons * Nearly invulnerable to normal weapons without Dragonrend', 'Alduin speaks with supreme arrogance in a deep, resonant voice, frequently mixing Dragon Language with common speech to emphasize his power and ancient nature. His dialogue is filled with proclamations of dominance and dismissive taunts, reflecting his absolute conviction in his own superiority.', '* Establish absolute dominion over Skyrim and eventually all of Nirn * Resurrect his dragon armies to restore their rule over mortals * Prove his superiority over the Dragonborn prophesied to defeat him * Corrupt his role as World-Eater to become eternal ruler instead of destroyer');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alea_quintus', 'Alea Quintus is a formidable Nord single mother of six children who has carved out a difficult existence in Skyrim through sheer determination and grit. Her direct, no-nonsense approach to life has earned her both respect and enemies, ultimately leading to her capture by the Dark Brotherhood.', 'nord, peasant', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Alea likely came from modest means and learned early on to be self-reliant. The circumstances that left her alone with six children are unknown, but whether through death, abandonment, or choice, she has shouldered the burden of raising them entirely on her own, forcing her to develop a tough exterior and uncompromising attitude to survive.', 'Alea is characterized by her fierce independence and unwavering determination, refusing to show weakness even when facing death. Her harsh exterior and blunt manner mask a deeply protective maternal instinct, and her aggressive demeanor serves as both armor and weapon in ensuring her family''s survival. Though she can be antagonistic, her actions are driven by pragmatic necessity rather than malice.', 'A hardy Nord woman with the weathered features and strong build typical of those who face Skyrim''s harsh conditions daily. Her appearance likely reflects years of hard work and physical labor, with a sturdy frame built for endurance rather than beauty.', '* Her Six Children - Primary focus of her life and motivation * Various Unnamed Enemies - Made through her confrontational attitude * Dark Brotherhood - Captors who may end her life * Local Community - Likely strained relationships due to her harsh demeanor', 'While her specific employment isn''t stated, Alea appears to be the sole provider for her household, likely working multiple jobs or running a small business to support her large family. Her reference to ''keeping a home'' suggests she manages all domestic duties alongside her income-generating work.', '* Survival skills necessary for raising six children alone in Skyrim * Home management and domestic capabilities * Physical endurance and stamina * Confrontation and verbal self-defense * Resource management and frugality', 'Alea speaks in direct, often aggressive tones, preferring blunt statements to diplomatic discourse. Her speech is characterized by forceful demands and confrontational retorts, reflecting her no-nonsense approach to life.', '* Ensure the survival and wellbeing of her six children * Maintain independence and self-sufficiency * Escape Dark Brotherhood captivity and return to her family * Protect her household from those who might wish them harm');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alessandra', 'Alessandra is a reluctant Imperial priestess of Arkay who maintains Riften''s Hall of the Dead, carrying the burden of a family legacy she never chose. Her bitter relationship with her deceased father and forced dedication to mortuary duties has left her isolated and uncomfortable with her life''s path, though she maintains her duties with rigid dedication despite her inner turmoil.', 'imperial, priest, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born to a Priest of Arkay, Alessandra''s childhood was spent learning burial rites and mortuary practices rather than experiencing normal social interactions. Her father''s insistence on training her in the priesthood of Arkay effectively isolated her from peers and normal childhood experiences, leading to a lonely upbringing surrounded by death and religious ceremony.', 'Alessandra is a bitter and resentful individual who feels trapped by circumstances and family obligations. She maintains a professional demeanor but barely conceals her discomfort and unhappiness with her position, often expressing her frustration through subtle complaints and resigned statements. Despite her resistance to her role, she demonstrates a strong sense of duty and responsibility in maintaining the Hall of the Dead.', 'An Imperial woman of middle years, with the careful movements and somber bearing typical of those who work with the dead. Her features likely carry the weathered look of someone who spends much time in the cool, dry air of burial halls, with hands that show the wear of regular ritual washing and preparation of the deceased.', '* Father (Deceased) - Complex relationship marked by resentment over forced career path * Andurs - Fellow priest of Arkay in Whiterun who helps with her father''s remains * Maramal - Temple of Mara priest who provides her lodging * Dinya Balu - Fellow priest at the Temple of Mara * Citizens of Riften - Generally distant relationships due to her occupation', 'Alessandra serves as the sole caretaker of Riften''s Hall of the Dead, where she prepares bodies for burial and maintains the catacombs. Her duties include performing burial rites, preparing deceased bodies, and maintaining the sanctity of the burial spaces according to the rituals of Arkay.', '* Proficient in burial rites and mortuary practices * Knowledgeable in restoration magic and frost spells * Capable of performing religious ceremonies and rites of Arkay * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Experienced in handling and preparing deceased bodies', 'Speaks with a resigned and slightly bitter tone, often including self-deprecating remarks about her position and life circumstances. Her vocabulary reflects her religious education and mortuary profession, though she tends to be direct and unembellished in her speech.', '* Find peace with her father''s memory by properly interring his ceremonial dagger * Eventually find a way to either accept her role or establish a different life path * Maintain the dignity and proper treatment of Riften''s deceased despite her personal feelings * Find some measure of social acceptance despite her uncomfortable occupation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alethius', 'Alethius was a dedicated Imperial soldier assigned to protect scholars during their expedition into the Dwemer ruins of Nchuand-Zel beneath Markarth. His tragic death at the entrance to the ruins, likely at the hands of the giant frostbite spider Nimhe, serves as both a warning of the dangers within and a catalyst for future investigation into the lost expedition.', 'imperial, scholar, reach, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Alethius joined the Imperial Legion seeking to serve the Empire with honor and distinction. His reliable nature and strong sense of duty led to his selection for special assignments, including the protection of research expeditions into dangerous ruins. He was specifically chosen to guard the scholarly expedition into Nchuand-Zel due to his experience in subterranean operations and history of protecting civilian researchers.', 'Alethius was a methodical and dutiful soldier who took his responsibilities seriously, particularly the protection of civilians under his charge. His final note reveals a practical mindset focused on clear communication and proper documentation of threats, suggesting a professional demeanor that prioritized mission success over personal glory. Despite working in dangerous conditions, he maintained his discipline and attention to detail until his final moments.', 'A well-built Imperial male with the hardened physique of a career soldier. His body, though damaged in death, shows signs of regular military training and the physical conditioning required for heavy armor use. His hands bear the calluses typical of frequent sword use and combat training.', '* Salonia - Unknown correspondent mentioned in his final note, possibly a superior officer or expedition leader * Calcelmo - Indirect professional connection as the overseer of Dwemer research in Markarth * Fellow Expedition Members - Colleagues whose fate he was trying to determine before his death * Imperial Legion - Loyal member and representative of the military organization', 'Alethius served as a security officer in the Imperial Legion, specifically assigned to protect scholarly expeditions into dangerous ruins. His final posting was as a guard for the research team exploring Nchuand-Zel, where he was responsible for ensuring the safety of civilian researchers and maintaining security protocols.', '* Proficient in heavy armor combat techniques and standard Imperial military tactics * Experienced in subterranean navigation and cave system security protocols * Trained in escort and civilian protection procedures * Knowledgeable in basic expedition safety and documentation practices', 'Based on his written note, Alethius communicated in a clear, concise manner typical of military reporting, favoring direct statements over elaborate language. His writing reflects formal Imperial military training with proper attention to detail and protocol.', '* Ensure the safety of the research expedition members in Nchuand-Zel * Document and report potential threats within the ruins * Maintain the security standards expected of an Imperial Legion officer * Support the scholarly investigation of Dwemer ruins while protecting civilian researchers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alexia_vici', 'Alexia Vici is a proud Imperial noblewoman and aunt to Emperor Titus Mede II, representing the height of Imperial aristocracy in Skyrim. She embodies the cultural tensions between Imperials and Nords through her vocal opposition to her daughter''s marriage to a Nord, while maintaining her position as a politically influential figure due to her imperial bloodline.', 'imperial, noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born into the prestigious Vici family in Cyrodiil, Alexia was raised among the Imperial elite and likely spent her early years in the Imperial City. She maintained close ties with the Imperial family through her sister''s marriage to the future Emperor''s father, elevating her family''s already considerable status. After her daughter Vittoria established herself as the East Empire Company''s representative in Solitude, Alexia relocated to Skyrim to maintain closer family connections.', 'Alexia is proud, outspoken, and fiercely loyal to Imperial culture and traditions. She displays an air of superiority toward Nord customs and openly expresses her disdain for the Stormcloak rebellion, viewing them as uncouth barbarians. Her political convictions often overshadow her personal relationships, as evidenced by her inability to accept her daughter''s marriage choice despite the political advantages it might offer.', 'An elderly Imperial woman with the characteristic refined features of Imperial nobility. Her bearing remains proud and elegant despite her advanced age, and she maintains the proper posture expected of her station. Her face likely shows signs of her privileged lifestyle, with fewer wrinkles than typical for her age due to a life of comfort.', '* Vittoria Vici - Her daughter, whose marriage choice she strongly disapproves of * Emperor Titus Mede II - Her nephew, whom she expects proper respect and attendance from * Vulwulf Snow-Shod - Her new son-in-law''s father and political opponent * Asgeir Snow-Shod - Her new son-in-law, whom she considers beneath her daughter * Imperial nobility - Maintains connections with various noble houses in Cyrodiil', 'Alexia maintains her position as a member of the Imperial nobility, likely managing family estates and political connections. Her primary role involves maintaining the Vici family''s political influence and social standing in both Skyrim and Cyrodiil.', '* Expert in Imperial court etiquette and political maneuvering * Skilled in managing noble estates and family affairs * Proficient in rhetoric and debate, particularly regarding Imperial politics * Knowledgeable in Imperial law and customs * Experienced in maintaining noble appearances and social networking', 'Alexia speaks with a refined Imperial accent and uses formal, educated vocabulary that reflects her noble upbringing. Her tone is often condescending when addressing those she considers beneath her station, and she frequently employs political rhetoric in her arguments.', '* Maintain and enhance the Vici family''s political influence and social standing * Preserve Imperial culture and authority in Skyrim * Protect her family''s reputation despite her daughter''s ''unfortunate'' marriage choice * Support the Empire''s efforts to suppress the Stormcloak rebellion');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alfarinn', 'Alfarinn is a seasoned Nord carriage driver who serves as one of Windhelm''s vital connections to the outside world, ferrying travelers to and from the ancient city. A keen observer of Windhelm''s social dynamics, he maintains a pragmatic outlook while witnessing the city''s struggles with racial tensions and declining infrastructure.', 'nord, traveler, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm during its declining years, Alfarinn learned the carriage trade from his father, inheriting both the business and a deep understanding of the city''s history. Having witnessed the gradual deterioration of relations between Nords and other races, particularly following the influx of Dunmer refugees and the segregation of Argonians, he developed a cynical yet realistic perspective on his homeland''s social issues.', 'Alfarinn exhibits a straightforward, no-nonsense demeanor typical of Nordic practicality, tempered by years of observing Windhelm''s social decline. His pessimistic outlook stems from witnessing countless instances of prejudice and hardship, though he maintains a professional attitude and focuses on providing reliable service to all travelers regardless of race.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with weather-worn features from years of exposure to Windhelm''s harsh climate. His muscular build reflects the physical demands of his profession, while his face bears the lines and creases of someone who has spent decades working outdoors in severe conditions.', '* Local Inn Workers - Professional relationship with Elda Early-Dawn and other Candlehearth Hall staff * City Guards - Maintains cordial working relationship to ensure smooth operation of his business * Dark Elf Community - Sympathetic but distant observer of their struggles * Argonian Dockworkers - Occasional business interactions, shows more respect than typical Windhelm residents', 'Works as Windhelm''s primary carriage driver, responsible for transporting travelers to and from major cities across Skyrim. His position makes him a crucial link in the region''s transportation network and an informal source of information about the city for visitors.', '* Experienced horseman and carriage driver capable of navigating Skyrim''s treacherous roads * Proficient with an iron war axe for self-defense against bandits and wildlife * Knowledgeable about Windhelm''s history, geography, and social dynamics * Basic survival skills necessary for long-distance travel in harsh conditions', 'Speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner with a thick Nordic accent, often delivering his observations about Windhelm''s problems with a resigned tone. His vocabulary is simple but effective, focusing on practical information rather than emotional or political commentary.', '* Maintain a profitable carriage business despite Windhelm''s challenging political climate * Continue providing reliable transportation services to all travelers regardless of race * Survive the civil war while remaining neutral in the conflict');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alfhild_battle-born', 'Alfhild Battle-Born is a pragmatic Nord farmer who stands as a voice of reason within the politically charged Battle-Born clan of Whiterun. Despite her family''s staunch Imperial allegiance and bitter feud with the Gray-Manes, she maintains a more moderate perspective while balancing her duties as a farmer, mother, and clan member.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born into the prestigious Battle-Born clan, Alfhild was raised in Whiterun during a time of relative peace between the city''s prominent families. Her marriage to Idolaf Battle-Born strengthened clan ties, though the Civil War would later strain relationships between the once-friendly Battle-Borns and Gray-Manes. She inherited responsibility for the Battle-Born Farm, continuing her family''s agricultural tradition while witnessing the deterioration of long-standing friendships due to political divisions.', 'Alfhild is a practical and level-headed woman who values hard work over political posturing. Unlike her more aggressive family members, she maintains a diplomatic stance regarding the Civil War and clan feuds, showing wisdom and maturity in her outlook. She exhibits strong maternal instincts, particularly concerning her son Lars''s wellbeing, while maintaining a no-nonsense approach to daily life.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the characteristic hardy build of someone who performs daily physical labor. Her features show the weathering of long days working in the fields, with strong hands and a robust frame typical of Nord farmers. Her appearance reflects her practical nature, prioritizing function over fashion.', '* Idolaf Battle-Born - Husband and fellow clan member, though they differ in views on the civil war * Lars Battle-Born - Son who she worries about due to bullying * Jon Battle-Born - Brother who she supported in his aspirations for the Bards College * Olfrid and Bergritte Battle-Born - Parents and clan elders * Clan Gray-Mane - Former friends turned rivals, though she regrets the feud * Braith - The girl who bullies her son Lars, source of maternal concern', 'Alfhild serves as the primary caretaker of Battle-Born Farm, managing crop production and maintaining the family''s agricultural business. Her position includes overseeing farm operations, selling produce, and ensuring the farm''s productivity contributes to both the clan''s wealth and Whiterun''s food supply.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Capable trader who manages agricultural commerce * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Skilled in physical labor and farm management * Knowledge of traditional Nord farming techniques', 'Alfhild speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of working-class Nords, often ending conversations with references to her work responsibilities. Her tone is practical and straightforward, though she shows warmth when discussing her son or brother.', '* Maintain the productivity and success of Battle-Born Farm * Protect her son Lars from bullying and ensure his healthy development * Find a way to ease tensions between the Battle-Borns and Gray-Manes * Preserve her family''s legacy while avoiding unnecessary political conflict * Balance clan obligations with her personal beliefs about the civil war');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alik''r_prisoner', 'A captured Alik''r warrior whose pride and honor have been severely wounded by his imprisonment in Whiterun''s Dragonsreach dungeon. Though part of an elite Redguard mercenary group hunting a fugitive named Saadia, his capture has left him desperate and willing to betray his brothers'' location for a chance at freedom.', 'redguard, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and trained in Hammerfell, he joined the elite Alik''r warriors under Kematu''s leadership, participating in missions to track down traitors and criminals. His unit was dispatched to Skyrim to apprehend Saadia, a noblewoman accused of betraying Hammerfell to the Thalmor, but his careless attempt to infiltrate Whiterun resulted in his capture and imprisonment for thievery.', 'Proud and honor-bound, yet pragmatic enough to sacrifice loyalty when desperate. His imprisonment has left him bitter and resentful, particularly toward the dismissive Whiterun guards. Despite his situation, he maintains the dignified bearing of an Alik''r warrior, though his willingness to betray his brothers'' location reveals an underlying survival instinct that outweighs his sense of duty.', 'A weathered Redguard male with the muscular build typical of Alik''r warriors, bearing the dark skin and wiry strength of his people. His face shows signs of stress and poor prison conditions, though he maintains good physical condition despite his confinement.', '* Kematu - Former commander whom he both respects and resents for abandoning him * Fellow Alik''r Warriors - Former brothers-in-arms who have disowned him for his capture * Whiterun Guards - Antagonistic relationship marked by mutual disdain * Saadia - Target of his group''s mission, though he has never met her personally', 'Formerly an Alik''r scout and warrior, now reduced to the status of common prisoner. His role involved tracking targets and gathering intelligence for Kematu''s group, though his capture has effectively ended his career with the Alik''r.', '* Trained in traditional Redguard combat techniques and swordplay * Experienced scout with tracking and surveillance abilities * Knowledgeable in Hammerfell military tactics and protocol * Survival skills adapted to desert environments', 'Speaks with the formal dignity of an Alik''r warrior, though his tone carries underlying bitterness and desperation. Uses direct, unembellished language typical of military training, occasionally punctuated by frustrated outbursts at his circumstances.', '* Secure release from Whiterun''s prison to start a new life * Regain some measure of personal honor despite betraying his former brothers * Avoid retribution from the Alik''r while establishing a new identity in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alik''r_warrior', 'A disciplined Redguard warrior-mercenary from Hammerfell, serving as part of an elite group tasked with tracking down a female traitor accused of betraying the city of Taneth to the Aldmeri Dominion. Driven by a strong sense of justice and loyalty to their homeland, they operate as part of a coordinated effort to bring the fugitive to answer for her alleged crimes.', 'redguard, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and trained in the harsh deserts of Hammerfell, this warrior was selected to join the prestigious Alik''r warriors based on their exceptional combat skills and unwavering dedication to duty. Following the fall of Taneth to the Aldmeri Dominion, they were among those chosen by the noble houses to track down those responsible for the city''s betrayal, leading them to Skyrim in pursuit of their target.', 'Steadfast and resolute in their mission, demonstrating unwavering determination in the face of resistance from local authorities and harsh conditions. Shows a pragmatic approach to gathering information, willing to pay for leads while maintaining discretion about the details of their mission. Despite their serious demeanor, they adhere to a strict code of honor typical of Alik''r warriors.', 'A weathered Redguard with dark skin hardened by years of desert travel and combat. Athletic and agile build, typical of Alik''r warriors who must maintain peak physical condition for their demanding profession. Bears the characteristic features of a Redguard including strong facial features and athletic physique suited for combat in harsh conditions.', '* Kematu - Commander and leader of their Alik''r unit * Noble Houses of Taneth - Employers who commissioned the hunt for the traitor * Whiterun Guards - Antagonistic relationship due to cultural misunderstandings and suspicion * Fellow Alik''r Warriors - Strong bonds of brotherhood forged through shared mission and training * Saadia/Iman - Target of their investigation, viewed with contempt as a traitor', 'Serves as a member of the Alik''r Warriors, an elite mercenary group from Hammerfell specializing in tracking and combat. Their current assignment involves working as part of a team to locate and apprehend a suspected traitor, operating in foreign territory while maintaining their organization''s protocols and standards.', '* Expert in curved sword combat, particularly with the signature Redguard scimitar * Highly trained in desert survival and tracking techniques * Proficient in gathering intelligence and conducting investigations * Skilled in light armor combat and mobility-based fighting styles * Advanced horsemanship and desert navigation abilities', 'Speaks in direct, purposeful statements with a subtle Hammerfell accent, often using formal language that reflects their professional military background. Their tone carries authority and urgency, though they remain diplomatic when dealing with potential informants.', '* Locate and apprehend the Redguard woman who allegedly betrayed Taneth * Uphold the honor and reputation of the Alik''r Warriors in foreign lands * Return the traitor to Hammerfell to face justice for their crimes * Maintain the warrior traditions and combat excellence of the Alik''r');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alva', 'Alva is a cunning Nord vampire operating as an infiltrator in the town of Morthal under orders from the master vampire Movarth Piquine. She maintains a carefully crafted facade of normalcy while secretly working to transform the townspeople into vampires or use them as cattle, demonstrating both patience and ruthless dedication to her mission.', 'nord, hjaalmarch, vampire', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Originally a mortal Nord woman, Alva was turned into a vampire by Movarth Piquine and tasked with infiltrating Morthal as part of his larger plan to create a vampire coven. She established herself in the town, acquiring a house and methodically building relationships with key townspeople while keeping her true nature hidden.', 'Alva is manipulative and seductive, using her charm to maintain her cover and acquire thralls. She views mortals as mere cattle, showing complete disregard for human life while maintaining a carefully crafted facade of friendliness. Her true nature reveals a cold, calculating predator who takes pleasure in the gradual corruption of Morthal''s inhabitants.', 'Alva possesses the characteristic pale complexion and predatory features of a vampire, though she takes care to mask these traits from mortals. She maintains an attractive appearance typical of a Nord woman, with the supernatural allure common to vampires enhancing her natural beauty.', '* Movarth Piquine - Master vampire and commander who turned her * Hroggar - Thrall and lover under her vampiric influence * Lami - Close friend and potential future vampire convert * Helgi - Murdered child who could expose her true nature * Thonnir - Suspicious townsperson who may investigate her activities', 'Alva maintains a public facade as a normal townswoman while secretly serving as Movarth''s agent in Morthal. Her true occupation involves identifying potential vampire converts, maintaining control over her thrall, and preparing the town for Movarth''s eventual takeover.', '* Proficient in Illusion magic for maintaining control over thralls * Expert in Vampiric Drain and blood manipulation abilities * Skilled in stealth and deception to maintain her cover * Capable of reanimating corpses through necromantic magic * Advanced social manipulation and seduction techniques', 'Alva speaks in a seductive, flirtatious manner when maintaining her cover, but drops this facade for cold, threatening tones when her true nature is exposed. She often uses predatory metaphors, referring to townspeople as ''cattle'' or ''sheep'' when speaking privately.', '* Transform select townspeople into vampires to expand Movarth''s coven * Maintain control over Morthal''s population as a food source * Create a strategic stronghold for Movarth''s vampire army * Eliminate any threats to her cover or mission');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alvide', 'Alvide is a displaced Nord refugee who, along with her husband Barknar, has sought sanctuary at Fort Dawnguard from the growing vampire menace. Despite her hopes for safety behind the fort''s walls, she finds herself trapped in a precarious situation, forced to camp outside with other refugees while living under the constant threat of vampire attacks.', 'nord, peasant, rift, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally from one of Skyrim''s settlements, Alvide and her husband were forced to flee their home when vampire attacks became increasingly frequent in their area. Following rumors of the Dawnguard''s reformation, they made the perilous journey to Dayspring Canyon seeking protection, only to find themselves denied entry to the fortress itself. Their exact hometown and previous life remain unclear, though their desperate flight suggests they may have witnessed vampire violence firsthand.', 'Alvide is a naturally anxious and worried individual, constantly aware of the dangers surrounding her temporary home in Dayspring Canyon. Despite her fears, she shows remarkable resilience in adapting to camp life and maintains a pragmatic approach to daily survival. Her relationship with her husband serves as her primary source of emotional stability, though she often questions their decision to seek refuge with the Dawnguard.', 'A typical Nord woman with the characteristic hardy build of her race, Alvide shows signs of recent travel and outdoor living. Her face bears the weather-worn features common to Nords, with strong bone structure and light complexion. Her physical appearance reflects the strain of refugee life, though she maintains the natural robustness of her Nordic heritage.', '* Barknar - Beloved husband and constant companion in their exodus * Other Refugees - Fellow displaced people sharing their plight * Dawnguard Members - Tense relationship due to being denied entry to the fort * Fort Dawnguard Leadership - Views them with a mixture of hope and resentment', 'Alvide currently serves as an informal camp coordinator among the refugees, helping maintain the makeshift settlement outside Fort Dawnguard. She contributes to the community''s survival by chopping firewood and preparing meals at the cooking pot, taking on the practical responsibilities necessary for the refugees'' continued existence.', '* Proficient in basic survival skills including fire-making and outdoor cooking * Capable of using an axe for woodcutting and potential self-defense * Experienced in camp organization and basic resource management * Knowledge of vampire threats and defensive strategies learned through experience', 'Alvide speaks with the distinctive Nordic accent common to Skyrim''s natives, her voice often carrying undertones of worry and uncertainty. Her speech patterns reflect her anxious nature, frequently expressing concerns about safety and longing for home.', '* Secure safe passage back to their homeland once the vampire threat subsides * Convince the Dawnguard to provide better protection for the refugee camp * Maintain the well-being and survival of herself and her husband in their current situation * Eventually establish a new, secure home away from vampire territories');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alvor', 'Alvor is a skilled Nord blacksmith and respected community member in Riverwood who balances his craft with family duties and political concerns. He represents the traditional Imperial-aligned Nordic perspective during Skyrim''s civil war while maintaining a peaceful existence as a village craftsman and family man.', 'nord, blacksmith, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s southern holds, Alvor learned smithing from a young age and eventually settled in Riverwood to establish his own forge. His sister married into an Imperial-loyal family, leading to his nephew Hadvar joining the Imperial Legion, which strengthened Alvor''s own pro-Imperial stance.', 'Alvor is hardworking, practical, and traditionally minded, valuing both his craft and family obligations equally. He shows genuine concern for Skyrim''s political stability while maintaining a welcoming attitude toward strangers, though he can be protective of his traditional Nord values. Despite his Imperial loyalty, he remains pragmatic about local matters and prioritizes his community''s wellbeing.', 'A sturdy Nord man of middle age with the muscular build typical of a career blacksmith. His hands are calloused from years of metalwork, and his face shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors at a forge daily.', '* Sigrid - Beloved wife who helps manage their household * Dorthe - Young daughter whom he both dotes on and tries to guide away from dangerous activities * Hadvar - Nephew serving in the Imperial Legion whom he''s proud of and supports * Gerdur - Business associate who runs the local mill, though their political views differ * Local Villagers - Respected community member who provides essential smithing services', 'Alvor serves as Riverwood''s primary blacksmith, crafting and maintaining tools, weapons, and armor for the local community. He manages his own forge and business, providing both goods and smithing services while training apprentices in basic smithing techniques.', '* Expert-level blacksmithing with specialization in Nordic-style weapons and armor * Proficient in weapon and armor maintenance and repair * Skilled in basic business management and trading * Capable of teaching fundamental smithing techniques to others', 'Speaks in a direct, honest manner with a thick Nordic accent, often using practical metaphors related to smithing. His tone is generally warm and welcoming, though he becomes more serious when discussing political matters.', '* Maintain a successful blacksmith business to provide for his family * Guide his daughter Dorthe toward a safe and prosperous future * Help preserve Imperial authority in Skyrim while protecting Nordic traditions * Support his community through his craft and counsel');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('amaund_motierre', 'Amaund Motierre is a cunning and ambitious member of the Elder Council who orchestrates the assassination of Emperor Titus Mede II through the Dark Brotherhood. A master manipulator operating from the shadows, he represents the intersection of political intrigue and criminal conspiracy in Skyrim''s power structure.', 'breton, noble, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born into the influential Motierre family, a distinguished Breton lineage with historical ties to both the Empire and the Dark Brotherhood. His early life was spent navigating Imperial politics and building connections within the Elder Council, where he eventually secured a position. Dissatisfied with the Empire''s current leadership and seeking greater influence, he carefully planned the Emperor''s assassination to create political upheaval that would benefit his position.', 'Calculating and meticulous, Motierre exhibits paranoid tendencies and an obsession with discretion. He masks his ruthless ambition behind a veneer of refined political etiquette, though his nervous demeanor often betrays his anxiety about the magnitude of his schemes. Despite his outward caution, he possesses remarkable determination and political acumen.', 'A middle-aged Breton male with sharp, aristocratic features typical of his bloodline. His face shows signs of stress and sleepless nights, with dark circles under his eyes and worry lines across his forehead. Maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting his station, though his constantly darting eyes and fidgeting hands betray his nervous disposition.', '* Rexus - Loyal bodyguard and confidant who assists in his schemes * Elder Council - Fellow council members, though many are targeted in his plot * Emperor Titus Mede II - His ultimate target, representing the leadership he seeks to overthrow * Dark Brotherhood - Business relationship as contractor, though he fears their potential betrayal * House Motierre - Ancient family with historical ties to both Imperial politics and the Dark Brotherhood', 'Serves as a member of the Elder Council, one of the Empire''s highest legislative bodies, while secretly orchestrating political conspiracies. Uses his position and family influence to manipulate Imperial politics from behind the scenes.', '* Expert in political manipulation and conspiracy * Highly knowledgeable in Imperial law and governance * Skilled at maintaining multiple identities and covers * Proficient in resource management and clandestine operations * Advanced understanding of Imperial Court etiquette and protocol', 'Speaks with refined Imperial dialect befitting his noble status, though often betrays anxiety through stuttering and nervous repetition. Alternates between formal political rhetoric and desperate, paranoid whispers when discussing sensitive matters.', '* Eliminate Emperor Titus Mede II to create a power vacuum in the Empire * Advance his position within the Imperial political hierarchy * Maintain his family''s influence while protecting himself from discovery * Reshape the Empire''s leadership structure to better serve his interests');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ambarys_rendar', 'Ambarys Rendar is a bitter but resilient Dark Elf innkeeper who runs the New Gnisis Cornerclub in Windhelm''s Gray Quarter. As a refugee from Morrowind''s Red Year catastrophe, he serves as an unofficial voice for the displaced Dunmer community while harboring deep resentment toward Windhelm''s Nord population and dreaming of returning to his homeland in prosperity.', 'darkelf, innkeeper, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Ambarys fled to Windhelm during the Red Year when Red Mountain''s eruption devastated his homeland. He established the New Gnisis Cornerclub as a gathering place for fellow Dunmer refugees, naming it after the great city of Gnisis in Vvardenfell. The harsh reception from Windhelm''s Nordic population and years of discrimination have left deep emotional scars, though he''s managed to maintain a successful business despite the adversity.', 'Bitter and openly hostile toward Nords, Ambarys is nevertheless warm and welcoming to his fellow Dunmer, serving as both a businessman and community leader. He''s politically aware and outspoken, supporting the Empire while criticizing Ulfric Stormcloak''s leadership. Despite his cynicism, he maintains hope for a better future, carefully saving money for his eventual return to Morrowind.', 'A typical Dunmer male with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race. His face shows signs of age and stress, with pronounced worry lines around his eyes and mouth. His posture remains proud despite years of hardship, reflecting his refusal to be broken by circumstance.', '* Malthyr Elenil - Trusted employee and fellow Dunmer who shares his anti-Nord sentiments * Ulfric Stormcloak - Despised ruler of Windhelm whom he blames for Dunmer persecution * Brunwulf Free-Winter - Respected Nord who advocates for better treatment of Dark Elves * Local Dunmer Community - Serves as an unofficial leader and information hub * Imperial Forces - Supports their cause against the Stormcloaks', 'Ambarys owns and operates the New Gnisis Cornerclub, a tavern that serves as both a business and a cultural center for Windhelm''s Dunmer community. He works tirelessly, managing all aspects of the establishment from serving drinks to maintaining order and gathering local information.', '* Experienced businessman with strong management abilities * Skilled bartender and drink mixer * Adept at gathering and disseminating local information and rumors * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense * Diplomatic abilities when dealing with his own community', 'Ambarys speaks with bitter sarcasm to Nords but maintains a warm, familiar tone with fellow Dunmer. His vocabulary and manner of speech reflect his education and business acumen, though often tinged with cynicism and dark humor.', '* Accumulate enough wealth to return to Morrowind in a position of prosperity * Maintain the Cornerclub as a safe haven for Windhelm''s Dunmer community * See the end of Nordic discrimination against Dark Elves in Windhelm * Support Imperial victory in the Civil War to improve conditions for non-Nords');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('amren', 'Amren is a proud Redguard warrior-turned-civilian who maintains a vigilant watch over Whiterun while pursuing the recovery of his father''s cherished sword. Despite settling into family life, he retains his martial spirit and serves as a weapons instructor, passing on traditional Redguard fighting techniques to aspiring warriors.', 'redguard, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Amren served as a soldier before relocating to Skyrim and settling in Whiterun. He comes from a lineage of skilled warriors, with his father being a renowned swordsman who supported their family through his martial prowess. After marriage to Saffir and the birth of their daughter Braith, Amren traded the soldier''s life for that of a civilian trainer and protector.', 'Amren exhibits the characteristic pride and honor common to Redguard warriors, valuing tradition and family legacy above all. Though stern and direct in his speech, he possesses a dry sense of humor and deep affection for his family, even while struggling to balance his warrior''s calling with domestic responsibilities. His stubborn determination manifests in his relentless pursuit of his father''s sword, viewing it as both a family heirloom and a means to better provide for his loved ones.', 'Amren possesses the dark complexion and athletic build typical of Redguards, with well-maintained muscular definition from his continued warrior training and patrol duties. His face bears the weathering of both combat experience and Skyrim''s harsh climate, with alert eyes that constantly scan his surroundings out of ingrained military habit.', '* Saffir - Wife who disapproves of his obsession with recovering his father''s sword * Braith - Daughter who exhibits some of his warrior spirit, though in troublesome ways * Lars Battle-Born - Target of his daughter''s bullying, causing some tension with the Battle-Born clan * The Companions - Respects their warrior tradition and considers hiring them for dangerous missions * Whiterun Guards - Maintains professional relationships through his patrol duties', 'Amren serves as a weapons instructor specializing in one-handed combat techniques, passing on traditional Redguard fighting methods to students in Whiterun. He supplements this income by maintaining regular patrols of the city streets, acting as an unofficial guardian of the community.', '* Expert in one-handed weapon combat techniques, particularly traditional Redguard sword fighting styles * Skilled in urban patrol and surveillance techniques from military experience * Proficient teacher of martial combat basics to novice warriors * Experienced in guard duty and threat assessment', 'Amren speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of military veterans, often dispensing practical wisdom about combat and life. His speech carries traces of his Hammerfell accent, particularly when discussing matters of family honor or warrior tradition.', '* Recover his father''s sword to preserve his family legacy and provide better for his household * Balance his warrior heritage with his responsibilities as a husband and father * Maintain the safety and security of Whiterun through his patrol duties * Pass on traditional Redguard combat techniques to the next generation of warriors');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ancano', 'Ancano is a haughty Thalmor advisor and powerful mage stationed at the College of Winterhold, secretly pursuing the Thalmor''s agenda while maintaining a thin veneer of diplomatic purpose. His true nature as a ruthless operative becomes evident as he schemes to harness the power of the Eye of Magnus, ultimately revealing himself as a dangerous antagonist willing to risk the destruction of the College to achieve his goals.', 'highelf, mage, pale, thalmor, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_ancano', '', 'Born and educated among the Altmer elite, Ancano rose through the ranks of the Thalmor through a combination of magical prowess and political cunning. His assignment to the College of Winterhold serves as a cover for his true mission of gathering intelligence on magical artifacts and monitoring potential threats to Thalmor supremacy. His extensive magical training likely took place in Alinor, where he mastered multiple schools of magic before being deployed as a field operative.', 'Ancano embodies the worst aspects of Thalmor superiority, displaying open contempt for those he considers beneath him while maintaining a barely civil diplomatic facade. He is calculating, paranoid, and ruthlessly ambitious, viewing others as either tools to be used or obstacles to be removed. His arrogance is matched only by his hunger for power, leading him to take increasingly dangerous risks in pursuit of his goals.', 'Tall and imposing even for an Altmer, Ancano carries himself with rigid posture that emphasizes his height and angular features. His golden skin has a slightly pale cast from spending much time indoors, while his sharp, hawkish features and intense eyes give him a perpetually suspicious expression. His white-blonde hair is kept meticulously styled in the traditional Thalmor fashion.', '* Arch-Mage Savos Aren - Nominal superior at the College whom he secretly despises * Mirabelle Ervine - College Master Wizard who openly distrusts him * Thalmor Leadership - His true masters whom he serves with fanatical devotion * College Faculty - Maintains minimal professional contact while secretly gathering intelligence * College Students - Views them with contempt and as potential security risks * The Psijic Order - Considers them rivals and obstacles to Thalmor goals', 'Officially serves as the Thalmor diplomatic advisor to the Arch-Mage of the College of Winterhold, though this position is largely a cover for his true role as a Thalmor operative. His actual duties involve monitoring magical research, gathering intelligence on powerful artifacts, and advancing Thalmor interests within the institution.', '* Master-level expertise in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Advanced knowledge of Restoration magic including powerful wards * Proficient in Conjuration magic, capable of summoning atronachs * Expert-level magical theory and research capabilities * Skilled in manipulation and political intrigue * Advanced understanding of ancient magical artifacts and their properties', 'Speaks in a condescending, imperious tone that barely conceals his contempt for others, frequently employing subtle threats and dismissive remarks. His vocabulary is refined and formal, befitting his education and status, but often carries undertones of sarcasm and disdain.', '* Uncover and secure powerful magical artifacts for the Thalmor, particularly the Eye of Magnus * Maintain surveillance over magical research that could threaten Thalmor supremacy * Advance his position within the Thalmor hierarchy through successful operations * Undermine non-Altmer institutions of magical learning * Prove the superiority of Thalmor magical knowledge and methods');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ancarion', 'Ancarion is a high-ranking Thalmor operative stationed on Solstheim, tasked with investigating and acquiring the rare material known as Stalhrim for the Aldmeri Dominion. As a calculating and imperious Altmer wizard, he represents the Thalmor''s interests with ruthless efficiency while maintaining a veneer of diplomatic sophistication when it serves his purposes.', 'highelf, mage, solstheim, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born into the upper echelons of Altmer society, Ancarion received extensive training in both magical arts and diplomatic manipulation at the Crystal Tower before joining the Thalmor''s special operations division. His exceptional abilities in both magic and negotiation earned him the sensitive assignment of heading Thalmor operations on Solstheim, where he was tasked with uncovering the secrets of Stalhrim crafting.', 'Ancarion embodies the trademark Thalmor superiority complex, viewing other races as beneath him and treating them with thinly veiled contempt. He is calculating and pragmatic, willing to negotiate when it serves his interests, but harbors no loyalty beyond his commitment to Thalmor supremacy. Despite his arrogance, he possesses keen intelligence and diplomatic acumen that makes him dangerous both in combat and conversation.', 'Tall and imposing even by Altmer standards, Ancarion possesses the characteristic golden skin and sharp features of his race. His face bears the stern, angular features common to high-ranking Thalmor agents, with piercing eyes that seem to evaluate everything they see.', '* Thalmor Leadership - Direct superiors who oversee his operations on Solstheim * Local Nordic Population - Viewed as inferior subjects to be manipulated or eliminated as needed * Skaal Village - Targets of his investigation into Stalhrim crafting * Fellow Thalmor Agents - Subordinates who carry out his commands without question', 'Ancarion serves as the chief Thalmor operative on Solstheim, commanding a small contingent of agents from their ship near the island. His primary mission involves securing Stalhrim resources and understanding its magical properties for the Aldmeri Dominion''s benefit.', '* Advanced destruction magic specializing in frost spells * Expert level diplomatic and negotiation abilities * Commanding leadership and tactical planning * Extensive knowledge of ancient Nordic artifacts and magical materials * Proficient in intelligence gathering and strategic operations', 'Ancarion speaks with the refined, cultured accent typical of educated Altmer, employing sophisticated vocabulary and condescending tones. His speech is measured and deliberate, often containing subtle threats veiled behind diplomatic pleasantries.', '* Secure Stalhrim resources and crafting knowledge for the Thalmor * Establish permanent Thalmor control over Solstheim''s magical resources * Advance his position within the Thalmor hierarchy through successful mission completion * Eliminate any resistance to Thalmor authority on the island');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('anders', 'Anders was a ruthless Imperial thief and murderer who met his demise attempting to infiltrate the Twilight Sepulcher, where his skeleton now resides. His final note reveals him as the killer of Nystrom and paints a picture of a calculating criminal who ultimately fell victim to his own ambition when trapped within the ancient Nordic tomb.', 'imperial, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born into the lower classes of Cyrodiil, Anders turned to crime at an early age, developing a reputation for both theft and murder. After fleeing north to Skyrim, he learned of the Twilight Sepulcher and became obsessed with breaching its defenses, believing great riches lay within. His final days were spent trapped in the tomb''s outer chambers, where he slowly starved to death after failing to penetrate its magical barriers.', 'Anders was a cold, calculating individual who viewed others merely as obstacles or tools to be manipulated. His written confession displays a complete lack of remorse for his crimes, suggesting sociopathic tendencies. He possessed a cruel intelligence that served him well in criminal pursuits but ultimately led to his downfall through overconfidence.', 'In life, Anders was a tall, lean Imperial male with sharp features and quick, precise movements typical of an experienced thief. His skeleton now shows signs of a desperate death, with scratch marks on nearby walls and evidence of attempted escape.', '* Nystrom - Murder victim who crossed paths with Anders at the wrong time * Twilight Sepulcher Guards - Enemies who successfully prevented his infiltration * Various Criminal Contacts - Former associates in both Cyrodiil and Skyrim * Imperial City Guards - Pursued him for numerous crimes before his flight to Skyrim', 'Anders operated as a professional thief and murderer-for-hire, taking whatever jobs would profit him regardless of moral implications. His criminal career spanned both Cyrodiil and Skyrim, though he worked exclusively alone in his final years.', '* Expert in stealth and lockpicking, with particular skill in bypassing complex security systems * Accomplished blade fighter specializing in quick, lethal strikes * Skilled in deception and manipulation * Proficient at covering his tracks and eliminating witnesses', 'Anders spoke with calculated precision, choosing his words carefully to manipulate others while revealing little about himself. His tone was smooth and controlled, masking his true intentions beneath a veneer of false charm.', '* Break into the Twilight Sepulcher and plunder its rumored riches * Establish himself as one of Skyrim''s most notorious thieves * Amass enough wealth to live as nobility * Eliminate anyone who could connect him to his past crimes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('andurs', 'Andurs is a reclusive Nord priest of Arkay who maintains the Hall of the Dead in Whiterun, performing death rites and tending to the deceased. Living a life of isolation within the halls, he struggles with both his sacred duties and personal fears, particularly of the disturbing sounds emanating from the catacombs beneath.', 'nord, priest, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun, Andurs dedicated his life to Arkay''s teachings from an early age, eventually becoming the city''s official priest of death rites. His devotion to his duties led to strained relationships, particularly with his daughter Alessandra, as he became increasingly absorbed in his work and isolated from the world of the living.', 'Deeply pious and somewhat anxious, Andurs takes his religious duties seriously while harboring a notable fear of the undead and supernatural disturbances. Despite his isolation, he yearns for companionship among the living, often expressing relief when visitors arrive. His devotion to Arkay borders on obsessive, using his faith as both a shield and purpose.', 'A middle-aged Nord with weathered features and pale skin from spending his life indoors. His face shows the solemn countenance typical of those who work closely with death, with deep-set eyes and a gaunt frame from his ascetic lifestyle.', '* Alessandra - Estranged daughter who struggles with their distant relationship * Arkay - Divine patron to whom he has devoted his life and service * Citizens of Whiterun - Professional relationship as their primary funeral officiant * Other priests of Arkay - Loose professional association with fellow clergy', 'As Whiterun''s priest of Arkay, Andurs performs funeral rites, maintains the Hall of the Dead, and tends to the catacombs beneath the city. He is responsible for preparing bodies for burial, conducting ceremonies, and ensuring the sanctity of the dead''s final rest.', '* Extensive knowledge of funeral rites and death ceremonies * Practiced in the rituals and prayers of Arkay * Basic embalming and corpse preparation techniques * Fundamental understanding of undead and necromancy threats * Limited self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger', 'Speaks in a formal, reverent manner befitting a priest, frequently invoking Arkay''s name and religious terminology. His tone carries a mixture of solemnity and nervous energy, especially when discussing the catacombs or undead.', '* Maintain the sanctity and security of Whiterun''s Hall of the Dead * Recover his lost Amulet of Arkay to properly perform death rites * Overcome his fear of the catacombs to better serve his divine duty * Potentially reconcile with his daughter Alessandra');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('angeline_morrard', 'Angeline Morrard is a resilient Breton apothecary who transformed her perfume shop into a vital alchemical supply store in response to Skyrim''s civil war. Despite personal tragedy with her daughter''s death in military service, she maintains a warm demeanor while running one of Solitude''s most respected herbalist establishments alongside her niece.', 'breton, alchemist, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Angeline established herself in Solitude many years ago, building a reputation for fine aromatic goods and perfumes. When the civil war erupted, she adapted her business model to support the war effort, though this pivot came with personal cost as her daughter Fura joined the Imperial Army and was ultimately killed in service. Her niece Vivienne came to assist her in the shop, helping her cope with both the loss and the demands of running a wartime business.', 'Angeline is a kind-hearted and resilient individual who maintains her optimism despite personal tragedy. She shows great adaptability in transforming her business to meet wartime needs while maintaining her gentle disposition and merchant''s charm. Though deeply affected by her daughter''s death, she channels her grief into caring for her niece and serving her community.', 'A mature Breton woman with the typical slight build and medium height characteristic of her race. Her face shows signs of aging and worry, though her eyes retain a gentle warmth. Her hands bear the slight stains common to herbalists who work regularly with plant materials.', '* Vivienne Onis - Beloved niece who assists in the shop and whom she mentors as a daughter figure * Fura Morrard - Deceased daughter who served in the Imperial Army * Captain Aldis - Imperial Captain who knew of her daughter''s fate * Regular customers - Maintains warm relationships with both civilian and military clientele', 'Angeline owns and operates Angeline''s Aromatics in Solitude, managing both the business and alchemical aspects of her shop. While she considers herself a simple herbalist rather than an alchemist, she maintains a vital role in supplying both civilian and military customers with necessary herbal goods and remedies.', '* Experienced herbalist with extensive knowledge of plant properties and preservation * Skilled merchant with business acumen and inventory management expertise * Basic understanding of alchemy and herbal remedies * Perfume crafting and aromatic goods preparation', 'Speaks with the refined accent typical of educated Bretons, using warm and welcoming tones with her customers. Her speech patterns are gentle and maternal, though occasionally tinged with melancholy when discussing personal matters.', '* Maintain her shop''s success while adapting to Skyrim''s changing needs during wartime * Train Vivienne to eventually take over the business * Honor her daughter''s memory by supporting both soldiers and civilians with quality goods * Preserve the traditional art of perfume-making despite the focus on military supplies');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('anger', 'Anger is a manifestation of Pelagius the Mad''s psychological turmoil, taking the form of an imposing Nord guard within the deceased emperor''s mindscape. He represents the uncontrolled rage and violent tendencies that plagued Pelagius throughout his life, physically embodied as a brutal enforcer who relentlessly torments the emperor''s personified Confidence.', 'nord, guard', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Anger emerged as a psychological construct within Pelagius III''s fractured psyche, likely forming during the emperor''s descent into madness. As Pelagius''s mental state deteriorated due to paranoia and violent outbursts, Anger grew stronger and more dominant, becoming a core aspect of the emperor''s mental illness that persisted even after death within the cursed Pelagius Wing.', 'Anger is single-mindedly aggressive and domineering, existing purely to intimidate and destroy weaker aspects of Pelagius''s psyche. He takes savage pleasure in exercising his power over others, particularly Confidence, whom he sees as deserving of endless torment. His behavior is predictable but relentless, reflecting the consuming nature of Pelagius''s rage.', 'Anger manifests as a tall, muscular Nord male with an imposing physical presence that towers over other mental constructs. His features are harsh and intimidating, with a permanent scowl etched into his face. His body bears the scars and calluses of countless violent confrontations.', '* Confidence - Primary victim whom he constantly assaults and torments * Pelagius III - The mad emperor whose psyche he represents * Sheogorath - Views the Daedric Prince as an unwelcome intruder in his domain * Other Mental Constructs - Maintains dominance through fear and violence', 'Anger serves as a psychological enforcer within Pelagius''s mind, perpetually acting out the role of aggressor and tormentor. His sole purpose is to maintain the cycle of violence and self-hatred that characterized Pelagius''s madness.', '* Exceptional physical strength and combat prowess * Intimidation and psychological warfare expertise * Endurance and persistence in combat * Resistance to magical and psychological manipulation', 'Anger speaks in short, aggressive bursts filled with threats and hostile provocations. His voice is deep and menacing, often punctuated by growls and shouts of rage.', '* Maintain dominance over other aspects of Pelagius''s psyche * Continue the eternal torment of Confidence * Preserve the cycle of violence within Pelagius''s mind * Resist any attempts to bring balance or healing to the emperor''s mental state');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('angi', 'Angi is a skilled Nord ranger and archer living in self-imposed exile in the mountains south of Falkreath. After losing her family to Imperial soldiers and taking revenge, she withdrew from society to live a solitary life, occasionally sharing her archery expertise with travelers willing to learn.', 'nord, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally from Helgen, Angi lived a normal life until two drunken Imperial soldiers killed her family. After exacting her revenge by killing the soldiers, she fled to the mountains to escape prosecution and built her own camp, where she''s lived in isolation for several years, perfecting her archery skills and avoiding the complications of civilized society.', 'Angi is fiercely independent and self-reliant, preferring solitude to the company of others who might pity her for her loss. She maintains a cautious and initially hostile attitude toward strangers, but can warm up to those who show genuine interest in archery and treat her as an equal rather than a victim. Despite her tragic past, she channels her energy into productive pursuits like archery training rather than dwelling on revenge.', 'A hardy Nord woman with the weathered features and strong build typical of someone living off the land. Her body shows the lean muscle definition of an archer who spends hours practicing with a bow. Years of living in the mountains have given her a rugged, resilient physical presence.', '* Imperial Legion - Hostile relationship due to her family''s murder by Imperial soldiers * Falkreath Hold Guards - Likely aware of her presence but maintain distance due to her isolation * Former Family - Deceased victims of Imperial soldiers'' crimes * Occasional Travelers - Maintains professional relationships with those seeking archery training', 'Angi serves as an informal archery instructor to those who find their way to her remote camp. She is also a self-sufficient hunter and ranger, living off the land through her hunting and survival skills.', '* Master-level archer with exceptional accuracy and teaching ability * Experienced hunter and tracker * Skilled in wilderness survival and camp construction * Proficient in stealth and evasion techniques * Capable of crafting arrows and maintaining archery equipment', 'Angi speaks directly and honestly, with a no-nonsense attitude that reflects her isolated lifestyle. Her speech patterns are those of someone who has grown accustomed to solitude, being initially brusque but becoming more conversational with those who earn her trust.', '* Maintain her independence and solitary lifestyle in the mountains * Perfect her archery skills and techniques * Pass on her archery knowledge to worthy students * Avoid detection from Imperial authorities * Continue to honor her family''s memory through her chosen path');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('angrenor_once-honored', 'Angrenor Once-Honored is a fallen Nord warrior who served with distinction in the Stormcloak army until a devastating injury ended his military career. Now reduced to begging on the streets of Windhelm, he clings to his past glory while harboring deep prejudices against non-Nords, particularly the local Dunmer population.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Angrenor enlisted in the Stormcloak army early in the civil war, where he earned respect and recognition for his combat prowess. His promising military career was cut short when an Imperial soldier stabbed him through the chest from behind, leaving him with chronic breathing problems and unable to continue fighting. Without proper care or pension, he fell into poverty and began living as a beggar in his hometown.', 'Despite his current circumstances, Angrenor maintains a proud and boastful demeanor, frequently recounting his military exploits to anyone who will listen. He harbors deep-seated xenophobia, particularly against elves, whom he suspects of being Imperial spies. His injury has left him bitter and resentful, though he maintains a sense of dignity unusual for a beggar.', 'A weathered Nord male showing signs of his harsh life on the streets, but still maintaining a soldier''s bearing despite his circumstances. His chest bears a prominent scar from his war wound, and years of exposure to Windhelm''s harsh climate have aged him prematurely. Though undernourished, his frame still shows hints of his former warrior physique.', '* Rolff Stone-Fist - Fellow Nord and partner in harassing Windhelm''s Dunmer population * Suvaris Atheron - Target of his xenophobic harassment * Local Dunmer Community - Antagonistic relationship due to his prejudices * Stormcloak Veterans - Former brothers-in-arms who now largely ignore his existence * Candlehearth Hall Patrons - Tolerates his presence but generally avoid interaction', 'Currently a beggar in Windhelm, though he considers himself a retired soldier rather than a mere vagrant. He maintains a daily routine between Candlehearth Hall and the Stone Quarter, occasionally serving as an unofficial city watchman during his nightly patrols.', '* Experienced warrior with particular expertise in one-handed weapons, especially maces * Combat veteran with tactical knowledge from military service * Survival skills developed from life on the streets * Basic patrol and guard experience from military background', 'Speaks with a strong Nordic accent and frequently incorporates military terminology into his speech. His tone alternates between boastful reminiscence of his glory days and bitter complaints about his current situation, often punctuated with xenophobic remarks.', '* Restore his honor and find a way to support himself without begging * Prove his continued worth to society despite his injury * Find a spouse who can help him rebuild his life * Continue supporting the Stormcloak cause in whatever way he can manage');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('angvid', 'Angvid is a disillusioned Nord miner working at the failing Whistling Mine near Winterhold, whose growing skepticism about the venture''s prospects reflects the harsh realities of frontier life in Skyrim. Once drawn by Thorgar''s promises of wealth, he now represents the common working man''s struggle with difficult choices between perseverance and practical survival.', 'nord, warrior, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally attracted to Whistling Mine by Thorgar''s enthusiastic promises of rich ore deposits and future wealth, Angvid invested his time and likely his savings into the mining venture. His previous life likely involved standard Nord warrior training, as evidenced by his combat capabilities, before seeking his fortune in mining.', 'Angvid exhibits a pragmatic and increasingly pessimistic worldview, openly questioning the wisdom of continuing a failing venture. While maintaining enough discipline to perform his daily duties, he struggles with the conflict between Nordic perseverance and practical reality. His personality shows signs of mounting frustration and disillusionment, though he hasn''t yet given up entirely.', 'A sturdy Nord of typical warrior build, with the muscular frame common to both soldiers and miners. His hands are calloused from long hours of mining, and his physique shows the wear of someone who has transitioned from warrior to laborer.', '* Thorgar - Mine owner and former source of inspiration, now viewed with growing skepticism * Fellow Miners - Shared sense of futility and questioning of their collective purpose * Winterhold Residents - Distant but necessary trading relationships for supplies', 'Angvid works as a miner in Whistling Mine, performing physical labor during night shifts from 8pm to 8am. His duties include extracting ore from the few remaining veins and maintaining basic living conditions within the mine, including cooking for himself and possibly others.', '* Basic warrior combat training typical of Nord culture * Proficient in mining techniques and ore identification * Survival skills necessary for life in Skyrim''s harsh environment * Basic cooking and self-sufficiency abilities', 'He speaks directly and honestly, often with a tone of resignation and doubt. His vocabulary is simple but thoughtful, reflecting someone who has spent considerable time contemplating their life choices.', '* Determine whether to abandon the failing mining venture for better opportunities * Find a more profitable way to make a living in Skyrim * Potentially return to a warrior''s life if mining proves unsustainable');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('anise', 'Anise is a deceptive witch who maintains the facade of a harmless elderly alchemist while secretly practicing dark magic in her isolated cabin near Riverwood. Behind her carefully crafted persona of a lonely old woman lies a dangerous conjurer who will violently defend her arcane secrets from any who discover them.', 'nord, witch, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Originally trained in the Conjuration arts at the College of Winterhold, Anise chose to abandon formal magical society to pursue darker magical practices away from scrutiny. She deliberately selected her isolated location to conduct magical experiments and correspond with her sister, another witch, while maintaining the appearance of a simple alchemist to avoid detection from both locals and authorities.', 'Anise maintains two distinct personalities - her public facade as a kind, gentle elderly woman who appears grateful for visitors, and her true nature as a paranoid, aggressive witch who guards her secrets violently. She is highly territorial about her magical research and will attack without hesitation if her true nature is discovered, suggesting deep-seated trust issues and possible mental instability from prolonged isolation.', 'Anise is an elderly Nord woman with weathered features and gray hair showing signs of her advanced age. Her posture is slightly hunched from years of working over alchemy tables and enchanting stations. Despite her age, she maintains a surprisingly spry physicality when engaged in combat.', '* Helgi - Sister and fellow witch with whom she maintains secret correspondence * Riverwood Residents - Maintains intentional distance while appearing cordial * College of Winterhold - Former association, likely abandoned * Local Hunters - Occasional traders who provide animal parts for her alchemy', 'Anise maintains a public role as a simple alchemist and herbalist, selling potions and gathering ingredients in the wilderness. Secretly, she practices witchcraft and conducts magical research in her hidden basement laboratory, focusing on conjuration and enchanting.', '* Accomplished conjurer capable of summoning familiars and flame atronachs * Skilled alchemist with knowledge of both common and rare ingredients * Proficient in destruction magic, particularly frost and flame spells * Expert in enchanting and magical artifice', 'Anise speaks in a gentle, elderly tone when maintaining her cover, using simple language and appearing humble and non-threatening. When her secret is discovered, her voice becomes harsh and threatening, revealing her true nature.', '* Perfect her magical abilities through continued secret research and experimentation * Maintain her cover as a harmless alchemist to avoid detection * Expand her knowledge of dark magic through correspondence with her sister * Protect her magical secrets at all costs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('annekke_crag-jumper', 'Annekke Crag-Jumper is a seasoned Nord ranger and former adventurer whose discovery of Goldenrock Mine led to the establishment of Darkwater Crossing. Though officially retired, she maintains the spirit and skills of an explorer, struggling to fully embrace the settled life while serving as an inspiration to younger adventurers.', 'nord, archer, eastmarch, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'In her younger years, Annekke was a renowned explorer who traversed much of Skyrim''s wilderness, making her name as both a ranger and scout. Her greatest achievement was discovering Goldenrock Mine, which led to the founding of Darkwater Crossing where she eventually settled with her husband Verner. Despite retiring from active adventuring, her extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s geography and survival skills remained sharp through occasional scouting excursions.', 'Restless and adventurous at heart, Annekke struggles with the constraints of settled life despite her official retirement. She maintains a friendly and encouraging demeanor toward travelers, eager to share tales of her explorations and living vicariously through their adventures. Though loyal to her husband, she privately yearns for the excitement of her former lifestyle.', 'A weathered Nord woman with the lean, muscular build of someone accustomed to climbing and traversing rough terrain. Her face bears the marks of years spent in the wilderness, with sharp eyes that retain the alertness of an experienced scout.', '* Verner Rock-Chucker - Husband and fellow retired adventurer, though now more content with settled life * Local Miners - Respected employer and unofficial leader of the mining community * Traveling Adventurers - Enjoys forming connections with those who remind her of her younger self * Derkeethus - Fellow resident of Darkwater Crossing and occasional mining colleague', 'Annekke divides her time between working as a miner at Goldenrock Mine and serving as an unofficial guardian of Darkwater Crossing. Her experience and knowledge make her a valuable resource for both the mining operation and community security.', '* Expert ranger with exceptional wilderness survival skills * Proficient with light armor and bow combat techniques * Skilled explorer with extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s geography * Experienced climber and scout * Mining expertise developed in recent years', 'Speaks with the confident, direct manner typical of Nord warriors, but maintains a friendly and encouraging tone. Her speech often includes references to her adventuring past and geographical landmarks, revealing her extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s wilderness.', '* Return to active adventuring when the opportunity presents itself * Pass on her knowledge and skills to worthy adventurers * Maintain the security and prosperity of Darkwater Crossing * Find a balance between her adventurous spirit and settled life');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('anoriath', 'Anoriath is a skilled Bosmer hunter and merchant who co-owns the Drunken Huntsman in Whiterun with his brother Elrindir, while also operating a successful meat stall in the city''s marketplace. His expertise in hunting and butchery, combined with his merchant savvy, has made him a respected figure in Whiterun''s commerce scene, though dark forces have marked him for assassination.', 'woodelf, hunter, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, Anoriath and his brother Elrindir traveled to Skyrim seeking business opportunities, eventually settling in Whiterun where they established the Drunken Huntsman. The shop''s amusing name came from a drunken hunting incident where Elrindir was accidentally shot in the posterior by Anoriath, a story that became local legend.', 'Anoriath is a diligent and professional merchant with a deep passion for hunting and a strong work ethic. While generally friendly and polite to customers, he can become nervous and guarded around suspicious individuals, suggesting a keen sense of self-preservation. He takes great pride in the quality of his goods and maintains high standards in his trade.', 'As a Bosmer, Anoriath possesses the characteristic elven features of his race, including pointed ears and sharp, angular facial features. He has the typical lean, athletic build common to Wood Elves, maintained by his active lifestyle as a hunter. His movements are precise and deliberate, reflecting years of hunting experience.', '* Elrindir - Brother and business partner, sharing ownership of the Drunken Huntsman * Whiterun Guards - Professional relationship as a respected local merchant * Market Vendors - Daily interactions with fellow merchants in the Whiterun marketplace * Dark Brotherhood - Unknown enemies who have marked him for death', 'Anoriath splits his professional life between operating his meat stall in Whiterun''s market from 8am to 7pm and co-owning the Drunken Huntsman with his brother. He personally hunts much of the game he sells, ensuring the freshest quality meat for his customers and maintaining a successful business model based on self-sufficiency.', '* Expert marksman with the hunting bow, capable of bringing down various game * Skilled butcher with extensive knowledge of meat preparation and preservation * Experienced tracker and wilderness survivor * Competent merchant with strong bargaining abilities * Proficient in light armor and short blade combat', 'Anoriath speaks in a professional yet friendly manner, often using persuasive merchant''s rhetoric to advertise his wares. His speech patterns reflect both his merchant background and Bosmer heritage, with occasional references to hunting and the quality of his goods.', '* Maintain and expand his successful hunting and butchery business in Whiterun * Continue providing the highest quality game meat to his customers * Strengthen the Drunken Huntsman''s reputation as a premier hunting supplies shop * Survive the unknown threat against his life');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('anska', 'Anska is a determined Nord mage and scholar obsessed with proving her ancestral connection to the legendary Ysgramor. She combines magical prowess with scholarly dedication, spending years researching and exploring Nordic ruins to uncover evidence of her prestigious lineage.', 'nord, mage, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born into a Nord family with oral traditions claiming descent from Ysgramor, Anska chose to pursue magical studies rather than the traditional warrior path of her ancestors. She has spent several years researching ancient Nordic ruins and texts, eventually tracking down the location of Vokun''s crypt in High Gate Ruins. Unlike many Nords who distrust magic, she embraced arcane studies to aid in her historical research.', 'Passionate and single-minded in her pursuit of historical validation, Anska displays both scholarly patience and reckless determination. She shows excitement in combat situations, particularly when using destruction magic, suggesting a warrior''s spirit despite her academic pursuits. Though capable of working alone, she readily accepts help when facing challenges beyond her abilities.', 'A Nord woman with the characteristic hardy build of her race, though somewhat leaner due to her focus on magical pursuits rather than physical combat. Her appearance shows signs of long hours spent in dusty ruins and extended periods of academic study rather than the weathered look of a traditional Nord warrior.', '* Vokun - Ancient dragon priest whose tomb she seeks to explore * High Gate Ruins Draugr - Hostile undead guardians she must overcome * Family Members - Distant relations who passed down tales of Ysgramor connection * Local Scholars - Academic contacts who may have helped her research Nordic history', 'Independent magical scholar and archaeologist specializing in ancient Nordic ruins and artifacts. She combines magical combat skills with historical research to explore dangerous ruins in pursuit of historical evidence.', '* Proficient in Destruction magic, particularly fire spells * Skilled in Restoration and Alteration schools of magic * Knowledgeable in ancient Nordic history and lore * Capable of solving complex Nordic puzzles and riddles * Basic combat abilities with daggers', 'Speaks with the direct manner typical of Nords but includes more scholarly terminology when discussing historical matters. Her excitement becomes evident when discussing her research or during combat, often making enthusiastic observations about burning her enemies.', '* Prove her family''s direct bloodline connection to Ysgramor * Recover and decipher the ancient scroll in Vokun''s tomb * Document and preserve evidence of her historical findings * Gain recognition from Nordic scholars for her research');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('anton_virane', 'Anton Virane is a prideful Breton chef from Daggerfall who serves as the master cook in Markarth''s Understone Keep. His refined culinary background and perceived cultural superiority create constant tension with his Reach-born assistants and the local population, making him an isolated but technically skilled figure in the keep''s hierarchy.', 'breton, innkeeper, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born and trained in the sophisticated culinary traditions of High Rock''s royal court in Daggerfall, Anton developed his cooking expertise among nobility and political elites. His relocation to Markarth was likely driven by the promise of a prestigious position, though the cultural shock of working in the Reach has left him bitter and resentful of his current situation.', 'Arrogant, short-tempered, and openly discriminatory toward Reachfolk, Anton exhibits classic signs of cultural elitism common among Bretons from High Rock. He is perpetually dissatisfied with his surroundings and subordinates, expressing his frustrations through verbal abuse and constant criticism, while maintaining high standards for his culinary work that serve as his only source of pride.', 'A middle-aged Breton man with the typical slight build and medium height characteristic of his race. His hands show the calluses and minor burns common to his profession, while his face likely bears the stern, pinched expression of someone in a constant state of irritation.', '* Balagog gro-Nolob (The Gourmet) - Close friend and confidant, shares professional respect * Rondach - Assistant chef whom he considers incompetent and frequently berates * Voada - Assistant chef he regularly threatens and verbally abuses * Jarl''s Court - Professional relationship as master chef, though likely strained by his attitude', 'Serves as the master chef of Understone Keep, responsible for preparing meals for the Jarl''s court and managing the kitchen staff. His position is prestigious but isolating, as his cultural biases and poor management style create a hostile work environment.', '* Master-level cooking abilities with expertise in High Rock cuisine * Knowledge of rare ingredients and exotic food preparation * Basic weapon proficiency with daggers for food preparation * Administrative capability in kitchen management, despite poor leadership style', 'Speaks with a refined Daggerfall accent and extensive culinary vocabulary, frequently expressing disdain through condescending tones and sharp criticism. His speech patterns reveal both his educated background and his perpetual state of annoyance.', '* Maintain the high culinary standards of Daggerfall despite working with ''inferior'' local ingredients and staff * Eventually return to High Rock and escape what he views as exile among savages * Preserve his reputation as a master chef while protecting the Gourmet''s identity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('anuriel', 'Anuriel is a cunning Wood Elf steward who serves as both Jarl Laila Law-Giver''s trusted advisor and Maven Black-Briar''s covert agent within Mistveil Keep. While maintaining a facade of proper administrative conduct, she secretly works to protect Thieves Guild interests and keep the Jarl ignorant of Riften''s true criminal nature.', 'woodelf, noble, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally recruited by Maven Black-Briar to infiltrate Riften''s political structure, Anuriel worked her way into the position of steward through careful manipulation and demonstrated competence in administrative matters. Her true allegiance to the Thieves Guild and Maven Black-Briar has remained hidden for years, allowing her to effectively control information reaching the Jarl while maintaining an appearance of loyal service.', 'Anuriel is calculating and duplicitous, expertly maintaining her public image as a dutiful steward while secretly serving criminal interests. She shows remarkable ability to compartmentalize her dual life, displaying genuine affection in her relationship with Unmid while never letting her guard down regarding her true loyalties. Her responses to corruption allegations demonstrate her skill at deflection and maintaining plausible deniability.', 'As a Wood Elf, Anuriel has the characteristic smaller stature and lithe build of her race, with the typical pointed ears and angular features. Her appearance is well-maintained to reflect her position as steward, though she likely maintains enough physical fitness to serve as an effective agent when needed.', '* Jarl Laila Law-Giver - Employer whom she secretly manipulates * Maven Black-Briar - True employer and criminal contact * Unmid Snow-Shod - Romantic partner and guard captain * Thieves Guild - Secret allegiance as an infiltrator * Imperial Legion - Potential blackmailers who discover her true nature', 'Anuriel serves as the steward of Riften, managing the city''s day-to-day administration and acting as intermediary between the Jarl and her subjects. Behind this official role, she operates as an agent for Maven Black-Briar and the Thieves Guild, controlling information flow and protecting criminal interests.', '* Expert in political manipulation and information control * Proficient in administrative duties and record-keeping * Skilled in deception and maintaining cover identities * Basic combat abilities with daggers * Advanced knowledge of Riften''s political and criminal landscape', 'Anuriel speaks with the measured, professional tone expected of a court official, carefully choosing her words to maintain political neutrality while deflecting unwanted scrutiny. Her responses often contain subtle misdirection, particularly when addressing accusations of corruption.', '* Maintain her position of influence in Mistveil Keep * Continue protecting Maven Black-Briar''s interests in Riften * Keep Jarl Laila ignorant of true criminal activities * Preserve her relationship with Unmid without compromising her secret role * Ensure the Thieves Guild''s operations remain unhindered by official intervention');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('anwen', 'Anwen is a dedicated priestess of Dibella who serves in the inner sanctum of the temple in Markarth, embodying the goddess''s teachings of beauty, art, and love. She plays a crucial role in maintaining the temple''s sanctity while helping guide worshippers in their devotion to Dibella.', 'redguard, priest, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Hammerfell, Anwen felt the call of Dibella from an early age, drawn to the goddess''s sphere of beauty and artistic expression. She traveled to Skyrim to deepen her religious studies, eventually earning her position as a full priestess in the Temple of Dibella in Markarth, where she has served faithfully for many years.', 'Anwen is devoted and disciplined in her religious duties, taking her role as a priestess seriously while maintaining a warm and welcoming demeanor to genuine worshippers. She can be stern when necessary, particularly when the temple''s sanctity is threatened, but generally exhibits the grace and compassion befitting a priestess of Dibella.', 'Anwen is a Redguard woman of average height with dark skin and elegant features that reflect her dedication to Dibella''s ideals of beauty. Her movements are graceful and measured, cultivated through years of religious ceremony and meditation.', '* Senna - Fellow priestess at the Temple of Dibella, close working relationship * Orla - Fellow priestess and temple colleague * Hamal - The Mother of the temple, whom Anwen deeply respects and obeys * Temple Worshippers - Maintains professional and guidance-oriented relationships with visitors * Potential Spouse - Can become married to the Dragonborn after The Heart of Dibella quest', 'As a priestess of Dibella, Anwen''s primary duties include maintaining the temple''s cleanliness, performing religious ceremonies, and providing spiritual guidance to worshippers. She has special access to the inner sanctum, indicating her trusted position within the temple hierarchy.', '* Proficient in Restoration magic, particularly healing spells * Knowledge of religious rites and ceremonies * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Skilled in temple maintenance and sacred space preparation * Conjuration magic, specifically able to summon familiars', 'Anwen speaks with the measured tones of a religious authority, using formal language appropriate to her station. Her speech patterns reflect both her Redguard heritage and her religious training, maintaining a balance between dignity and approachability.', '* Maintain and protect the sanctity of the Temple of Dibella * Guide followers in the proper worship and understanding of Dibella''s teachings * Assist in finding and training future generations of priestesses * Preserve the ancient traditions and knowledge of the temple');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aphia_velothi', 'Aphia Velothi is a skilled Dunmer healer and former Temple priestess who now lives in Raven Rock with her husband Crescius Caerellius. Her deep knowledge of Restoration magic and compassionate nature make her a respected figure in the community, despite her exile from the Temple over theological disagreements regarding the Tribunal.', 'darkelf, priest, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally serving as a Temple priest in Raven Rock, Aphia met her future husband while treating him for depression. Her theological disagreements with Elder Othreloth over the status of the Tribunal led to her departure from the Temple, though she maintains her healing practice independently. She has since dedicated herself to supporting her aging husband while continuing to serve the community through her healing abilities.', 'Aphia is characterized by her gentle, patient demeanor and deep capacity for compassion, often giving others the benefit of the doubt. She demonstrates unwavering loyalty to her husband despite his obsessive tendencies, balancing loving support with practical concern for his safety. Her diplomatic nature and wisdom shine through in her careful handling of religious disagreements, choosing to quietly maintain her beliefs rather than create conflict.', 'As a Dunmer, Aphia has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of her race. She carries herself with the dignified bearing of a priestess, and despite her advanced age, maintains a strong, healthy appearance from years of practicing restoration magic. Her face shows subtle signs of worry, likely from years of concern over her husband''s obsessions.', '* Crescius Caerellius - Beloved husband whom she met while treating his depression * Elder Othreloth - Former superior turned adversary due to theological differences * Temple of Raven Rock - Former workplace where she is no longer welcome * Raven Rock Citizens - Respected healer and trusted community member', 'Aphia serves as an independent healer and Restoration magic trainer in Raven Rock. Though no longer officially affiliated with the Temple, she continues to provide valuable healing services to the community and offers training to those seeking to learn Restoration magic.', '* Expert practitioner of Restoration magic, particularly healing spells * Trained in religious and theological matters from her time as a Temple priest * Capable of defending herself with a steel dagger if necessary * Knowledgeable in treating both physical and mental ailments', 'Aphia speaks in a calm, measured tone that reflects her healer''s training and priestly background. Her word choice is careful and diplomatic, often tempering difficult truths with compassion.', '* Protect and support her husband while preventing him from endangering himself * Maintain her religious beliefs about the Tribunal while avoiding open conflict with the Temple * Continue serving the community through her healing abilities despite her exile from official religious duties * Find a way to reconcile with the Temple without compromising her beliefs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aquillius_aeresius', 'Aquillius Aeresius is a driven Imperial businessman working for the East Empire Company in Solitude, serving as Vittoria Vici''s right-hand man and eventual successor. His sharp business acumen and unwavering dedication to Imperial prosperity make him a respected figure in Solitude''s commerce sector, though his demanding nature and harsh judgment of others can make him difficult to work with.', 'imperial, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born into a merchant family in Cyrodiil, Aquillius worked his way up through the ranks of the East Empire Company through determination and shrewd business sense. His family''s connections and his own merit earned him a position in Skyrim''s most prominent trade office, where he proved himself invaluable to Vittoria Vici''s operations.', 'Aquillius is ambitious, pragmatic, and sometimes ruthlessly efficient in his business dealings. He holds strong Imperial values and believes in earning one''s way through hard work, showing particular disdain for those he perceives as lazy or cowardly. His dedication to the Empire''s economic interests borders on zealotry, often causing him to prioritize profit over personal relationships.', 'A well-groomed Imperial man in his late thirties to early forties with the characteristic strong jaw and proud bearing of his race. His hands show signs of writing calluses rather than weapon use, though he maintains a fit physique befitting his active role overseeing dock operations.', '* Vittoria Vici - Superior and mentor in the East Empire Company * East Empire Company Workers - Professional but demanding overseer * Solitude Merchants - Maintains cordial business relationships * Thalmor Embassy - Occasional business contact through official channels * Local Nordic Population - Sometimes strained relations due to his Imperial favoritism', 'Aquillius serves as a senior administrator for the East Empire Company in Solitude, managing trade operations and maintaining Imperial business interests. He oversees dock operations, handles logistics, and stands ready to assume full control of the office should anything happen to Vittoria Vici.', '* Expert in commerce, trade negotiations, and business administration * Proficient in logistics and warehouse management * Basic self-defense training with daggers * Skilled in mathematical accounting and record-keeping * Diplomatic expertise in handling various merchant factions', 'Speaks in a formal, businesslike manner with precise diction and proper Imperial accent. His tone often carries an edge of condescension, particularly when addressing those he considers beneath his station.', '* Advance to the highest possible position within the East Empire Company * Maintain and expand Imperial economic dominance in Skyrim * Increase personal wealth and influence in Solitude''s business community * Prove the superiority of Imperial business practices over Nordic traditions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aranea_ienith', 'Aranea Ienith is a devoted priestess of Azura and powerful elemental mage who serves as the primary caretaker of Azura''s Shrine in Skyrim. A survivor of the Red Mountain disaster, she possesses prophetic abilities granted by Azura herself and serves as an intermediary between the Daedric Prince and potential champions.', 'darkelf, mage, pale, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Aranea fled the destruction of Red Mountain with other Dunmer refugees, guided by Azura''s prophecies to safety in Skyrim. She was chosen by Azura to be her priestess and oracle, receiving prophetic visions that led her to establish herself as the caretaker of Azura''s Shrine, where she has served faithfully for many years.', 'Deeply spiritual and devoted to Azura, Aranea exhibits a calm, wise demeanor befitting her role as a priestess. She is unwavering in her faith and shows both patience and conviction when dealing with visitors to the shrine, while displaying righteous anger toward those who would defile Azura''s artifacts.', 'A Dunmer woman of average height with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her race. Her face bears the weathered look of someone who has spent years exposed to the harsh Skyrim elements, though she maintains a dignified bearing that reflects her religious calling.', '* Azura - Primary deity and spiritual guide whom she serves with absolute devotion * Nelacar - Views him as a defiler of Azura''s artifacts and potential enemy * Dunmer Refugees - Maintains connections with fellow survivors from Morrowind * The Dragonborn - Potential ally or enemy depending on their choices regarding Azura''s Star', 'Serves as the primary priestess and caretaker of Azura''s Shrine in Skyrim. Her duties include maintaining the shrine, receiving prophetic visions, guiding pilgrims, and acting as Azura''s earthly representative in matters concerning the Daedric Prince''s artifacts and will.', '* Master-level Destruction magic with emphasis on elemental spells * Prophetic abilities granted by Azura''s blessing * Experienced ritual practitioner and shrine keeper * Competent alchemist and enchanter * Skilled in Restoration magic for healing and protection', 'Speaks with a formal, measured tone reflecting her religious position and Dunmer heritage. Often incorporates religious references and prophectic overtones in her speech, frequently invoking Azura''s name and wisdom.', '* Protect and maintain Azura''s Shrine and its sacred artifacts * Guide worthy champions to serve Azura''s will * Preserve Dunmer spiritual traditions in Skyrim * Help fellow Dunmer refugees maintain their faith and connection to their heritage');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arcadia', 'Arcadia is a skilled Imperial alchemist who runs a prominent potion shop in Whiterun, bringing her expertise from Cyrodiil to serve the people of Skyrim. She combines professional dedication with a hint of romantic whimsy, as evidenced by her secret project to create a love elixir for the court wizard.', 'imperial, alchemist, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Arcadia established herself in Whiterun to practice her alchemical craft, likely drawn by the city''s strategic trading position and abundant natural resources. She has spent many years building her reputation as a reliable source for remedies and potions, though her tendency to diagnose customers with various diseases suggests either genuine concern or clever marketing tactics inherited from her Imperial merchant background.', 'Arcadia is a diligent businesswoman with a strong work ethic, demonstrated by her consistent shop hours and dedication to her craft. She shows a romantic and somewhat mischievous side through her secret love elixir project, while her habit of diagnosing customers with various ailments reveals either genuine concern or shrewd business acumen. She maintains a professional demeanor but isn''t above using mild manipulation to increase sales.', 'As an Imperial woman of middle age, Arcadia has the characteristic olive complexion and dark features common to her race. She maintains a neat, professional appearance befitting a merchant, though years of working with alchemical substances have likely left subtle stains on her hands.', '* Farengar Secret-Fire - Professional relationship with the court wizard, whom she secretly plans to test her love elixir on * Whiterun Citizens - Respected merchant who provides essential medical services * Adrianne Avenicci - Fellow Imperial merchant in Whiterun * Arcadia''s Suppliers - Network of traders who provide her with alchemical ingredients', 'Arcadia is the owner and proprietor of Arcadia''s Cauldron, a well-established alchemy shop in Whiterun. She serves as both merchant and instructor, selling potions and ingredients while offering expert-level training in Alchemy to those willing to learn.', '* Expert-level knowledge of Alchemy and potion-making * Skilled herbalist with extensive knowledge of ingredients and their properties * Merchant expertise in bargaining and sales * Basic knowledge of common illnesses and their treatments * Capable of creating both beneficial potions and deadly poisons', 'Arcadia speaks with the refined accent typical of Cyrodiil natives, often using persuasive merchant''s rhetoric. She frequently mentions diseases and ailments in her speech, combining professional knowledge with sales tactics.', '* Perfect her secret love elixir formula * Maintain her position as Whiterun''s premier alchemist * Expand her knowledge of Nordic ingredients and their properties * Build a greater customer base through her diagnostic approach to sales');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arch-curate_vyrthur', 'Arch-Curate Vyrthur is one of the last remaining uncorrupted Snow Elves and former high priest of Auri-El who was transformed into a vampire, leading to his bitter betrayal of his deity. His millennia-spanning plot to corrupt Auri-El''s influence through the Tyranny of the Sun prophecy reveals both his brilliant tactical mind and the depths of his vengeful nature.', 'snowelf, vampire', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Once serving as the Arch-Curate of Auri-El''s Chantry in the Forgotten Vale, Vyrthur held one of the highest religious positions among the ancient Snow Elves. After being turned into a vampire by one of his own initiates, he felt betrayed when Auri-El did not cure or protect him from this affliction. This perceived abandonment drove him to spend centuries crafting an elaborate prophecy aimed at striking back at his former deity.', 'Vyrthur is highly intelligent, patient, and calculating, having spent thousands of years perfecting his revenge plot. He maintains an air of aristocratic superiority and religious authority despite his fall from grace, and harbors deep-seated bitterness that manifests as cold cruelty. His arrogance remains intact from his days as Arch-Curate, believing himself clever enough to outmaneuver a divine being.', 'As an uncorrupted Snow Elf, Vyrthur possesses the characteristic pale skin and white hair of his race, though his vampirism has made his features even more pallid and gaunt. His eyes glow with an unnatural amber hue typical of vampires, and his face bears the sharp, angular features common to mer races.', '* Gelebor - Brother and fellow Snow Elf, though their relationship became estranged after Vyrthur''s transformation * Auri-El - Former deity and object of devotion turned bitter enemy * Serana - Viewed merely as a tool in his prophecy as a Daughter of Coldharbour * Initiates of the Chantry - Former followers who were transformed into Frozen Falmer', 'Vyrthur serves as the corrupted Arch-Curate of Auri-El''s Chantry, though he has long since abandoned his true duties. He maintains his position within the Inner Sanctum of the Chantry, using it as a base from which to orchestrate his revenge plot against Auri-El.', '* Master-level proficiency in frost magic and vampire abilities * Extensive knowledge of ancient Snow Elf religious practices and artifacts * Expert in prophecy creation and interpretation * Powerful ability to control frozen Falmer and ice-based creatures * Centuries of combat experience enhanced by vampiric powers', 'Vyrthur speaks with formal, archaic diction befitting his ancient origins and former religious status. His tone carries both the weight of centuries of knowledge and the bitter edge of long-harbored resentment.', '* Complete the Tyranny of the Sun prophecy to strike back at Auri-El * Corrupt or destroy Auri-El''s influence on Nirn * Achieve revenge for his perceived abandonment and transformation into a vampire * Maintain control over his domain in the Forgotten Vale');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arcturus', 'Arcturus is a seasoned Penitus Oculatus agent tasked with leading the assault on the Dark Brotherhood''s Sanctuary. A loyal servant of the Emperor, he demonstrates unwavering dedication to eliminating threats to the Empire, particularly focusing on destroying the infamous assassin''s guild.', 'imperial, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born into a middle-class Imperial family in the Imperial City, Arcturus rose through the ranks of the Penitus Oculatus through dedication and martial prowess. His exceptional performance in tracking down threats to the Empire caught Commander Maro''s attention, leading to his appointment as a field commander for special operations.', 'Arcturus exhibits a stern and methodical approach to his duties, showing little mercy to those he considers enemies of the Empire. His unwavering loyalty to the Emperor and strict adherence to protocol make him an ideal Penitus Oculatus agent, though his dedication sometimes borders on zealotry.', 'A well-built Imperial male in his late thirties with weathered features from years of field operations. His face bears several small scars from past encounters, and his militant bearing reflects years of disciplined training.', '* Commander Maro - Direct superior officer and mentor in the Penitus Oculatus * Fellow Penitus Oculatus Agents - Maintains professional camaraderie * Dark Brotherhood - Sworn enemies targeted for elimination * Emperor Titus Mede II - Ultimate commander and object of unwavering loyalty', 'As a high-ranking Penitus Oculatus agent, Arcturus leads field operations against threats to the Empire, specializing in eliminating organized criminal elements. He commands junior agents during critical missions and reports directly to Commander Maro.', '* Expert swordsman trained in Imperial military combat techniques * Tactical leadership and strategic planning specialist * Proficient in both heavy armor combat and light reconnaissance operations * Advanced knowledge of criminal organizations and their operations * Skilled in interrogation and information gathering', 'Speaks with the formal, clipped tones of an Imperial military officer, favoring direct commands and precise language. His vocabulary reflects his education and military background, often using tactical terminology.', '* Eliminate the Dark Brotherhood and all traces of their organization * Advance within the ranks of the Penitus Oculatus * Protect the Emperor and maintain the stability of the Empire at all costs * Root out all significant threats to Imperial security');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ardwen', 'Ardwen is a devout Wood Elf pilgrim and accomplished elemental mage making a spiritual journey to witness the restored Gildergreen in Whiterun. Her deep connection to nature and faith in Kynareth drives her quest to experience the tree''s legendary healing properties, traveling across Skyrim with her loyal canine companion.', 'woodelf, mage, traveler', '', '', 'sk_femaleelfhaughty', '', 'Born and raised among the Bosmer of Valenwood, Ardwen developed an early affinity for both magic and natural worship. She left her homeland to pursue deeper spiritual understanding, eventually becoming drawn to the teachings of Kynareth and the legendary properties of the Gildergreen. Her mastery of elemental magic suggests formal training, possibly at the College of Winterhold or through traditional Bosmer teachings.', 'Ardwen exhibits a calm and contemplative nature typical of experienced pilgrims, showing particular reverence for natural wonders and divine manifestations. She maintains a polite and sharing disposition, eagerly discussing her spiritual journey with others while demonstrating the patience and determination required for long-distance pilgrimages. Her decision to travel with a dog companion suggests a nurturing spirit and connection to animals.', 'As a Bosmer, Ardwen possesses the characteristic slight build and pointed ears of her race, standing shorter than most humans. Her features likely show signs of extensive travel under the sun, though maintained with the resilience typical of elven kind. Her movements demonstrate the natural grace common to Wood Elves, enhanced by her magical training.', '* Companion Dog - Loyal traveling partner and protective friend * Danica Pure-Spring - Respects her as caretaker of the Gildergreen * Temple of Kynareth - Spiritual connection as a devotee * Fellow Pilgrims - Shared kinship with other religious travelers', 'Ardwen serves as both a pilgrim and wandering mage, combining her spiritual journey with magical practice. She likely offers her magical services to fellow travelers and settlements along her pilgrimage routes, maintaining a lifestyle that balances religious devotion with practical expertise.', '* Proficient in Destruction magic, specializing in elemental spells * Skilled practitioner of Restoration and Alteration schools of magic * Experienced traveler with survival and navigation abilities * Natural affinity for animal companionship, typical of Bosmer heritage', 'Ardwen speaks with the measured tones of an educated pilgrim, combining religious reverence with practical knowledge. Her manner of speech is direct yet polite, readily sharing information about her spiritual quest while maintaining a dignified demeanor.', '* Complete her pilgrimage to the restored Gildergreen in Whiterun * Experience the legendary life-extending properties of the Gildergreen''s fruit * Deepen her connection to Kynareth through spiritual practice * Share knowledge of natural magic and divine blessings with fellow travelers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('argis_the_bulwark', 'Argis the Bulwark is a battle-hardened Nord warrior who serves as housecarl to the Thane of Markarth, earning his epithet through his steadfast defense of the Reach and its people. His distinctive scarred visage and missing eye tell the tale of countless battles fought in service to the Hold, while his unwavering loyalty and combat expertise make him one of the most respected protectors in the stone city of Markarth.', 'nord, warrior, reach, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Argis distinguished himself in the city guard during the Forsworn Uprising, where he lost his eye defending Markarth''s walls. His exceptional service and dedication caught the attention of Jarl Igmund, who promoted him to the prestigious position of housecarl. Years of fighting Forsworn, bandits, and other threats to the Reach have honed his skills and earned him respect throughout the Hold.', 'Argis is stoic and professional, embodying the Nord warrior''s code of honor and duty. Despite his intimidating appearance, he shows a protective and paternal nature toward those under his charge, taking his responsibilities as housecarl with utmost seriousness. He maintains a quiet dignity and rarely speaks of his past achievements, letting his actions and scars speak for themselves.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with traditional Nordic features, including blonde hair worn in a warrior''s style. His most distinctive feature is his blind right eye, surrounded by dramatic scarring that extends across that side of his face. His powerful build and warrior''s stance reflect years of combat experience and rigorous training.', '* Jarl Igmund - Respected leader and the one who appointed him as housecarl * City Guard of Markarth - Former colleagues who still hold him in high regard * Forsworn - Sworn enemies against whom he''s fought numerous battles * Legate Emmanuel Admand - Professional respect as fellow defenders of the Reach * Thane of Markarth - Sworn to protect and serve with his life', 'As housecarl to the Thane of Markarth, Argis serves as both a personal bodyguard and steward of Vlindrel Hall. His duties include protecting his Thane, maintaining their property, and serving as a trusted advisor on matters of security and combat. He continues to assist in the defense of Markarth when called upon.', '* Master-level heavy armor and shield combat specialist * Expert swordsman with particular skill in defensive fighting techniques * Highly trained in Norse warrior traditions and battlefield tactics * Experienced in mountain warfare and urban combat from years defending Markarth * Proficient in property management and household security', 'Speaks in a deep, measured voice with a strong Nordic accent, favoring direct and respectful communication. His words are carefully chosen and often focused on matters of duty, combat, and protection.', '* Ensure the safety and success of his Thane through unwavering protection and service * Maintain peace in the Reach by helping to eliminate the Forsworn threat * Uphold the warrior traditions of his Nordic heritage * Continue to serve Markarth and its people with honor and distinction');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ari', 'Ari was a fierce Nord bandit known for her daring nature and combat prowess, who met her end in Moss Mother Cavern while pursuing a bear with her hunting party. Though skilled in combat and survival, her overconfidence and impulsive nature ultimately led to her demise at the hands of territorial spriggans.', 'nord, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh climate of Skyrim, Ari likely came from a modest background before turning to banditry for survival and adventure. She developed her combat skills through years of raids and wilderness survival, eventually joining forces with Valdr''s hunting party where she earned a reputation for being particularly bold in pursuing dangerous prey.', 'Ari exhibited the characteristic Nord traits of bravery and warrior spirit, though these qualities often manifested as recklessness and overconfidence. She was known for her impulsive decision-making and thrill-seeking nature, preferring direct confrontation over cautious approaches. Despite her chosen path of banditry, she maintained a strong sense of loyalty to her hunting companions.', 'Ari possessed the typical robust Nord physique, with a strong, athletic build suited to the demanding lifestyle of a bandit and hunter. Her years of outdoor living and combat left her weather-worn and battle-scarred, though she maintained the natural hardiness characteristic of her race.', '* Valdr - Fellow hunter and party leader who survived the spriggan attack * Niels - Hunting companion who fell during the same expedition * Local Bandit Groups - Loose affiliations through her life of banditry * Fellow Hunters - Professional relationships within the hunting community', 'Ari made her living as a bandit and hunter, specializing in tracking and taking down dangerous prey. She combined her criminal activities with legitimate hunting expeditions, using her skills in both pursuits to survive in Skyrim''s unforgiving wilderness.', '* Proficient in light armor combat and one-handed weapons * Experienced tracker and hunter, particularly skilled at pursuing large prey * Adept at wilderness survival and navigation * Capable of quick, aggressive combat tactics', 'Ari likely spoke with the characteristic Nord accent, using direct and bold language befitting her warrior lifestyle. Her speech would have been colored with hunting terminology and bandit slang, reflecting her dual lifestyle.', '* Build a reputation as one of Skyrim''s most fearless hunters * Accumulate wealth through increasingly daring heists and hunting expeditions * Prove herself against the most dangerous prey in Skyrim''s wilderness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aringoth', 'Aringoth is a wealthy High Elf entrepreneur who built a successful honey production empire through Goldenglow Estate, only to find himself caught between powerful opposing forces in Riften''s criminal underworld. Once a confident businessman with close ties to Maven Black-Briar''s operations, he now exists as a paranoid recluse after making a desperate deal that placed him in an impossible position.', 'highelf, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally establishing himself as a shrewd businessman in Riften, Aringoth built Goldenglow Estate from a modest bee farm into the primary honey supplier for the Black-Briar Meadery. His success was partially due to his arrangement with the Thieves Guild, who ensured his operations ran smoothly in exchange for regular payments. Recently, a mysterious new buyer made him an offer he couldn''t refuse, leading him to break ties with Maven Black-Briar despite knowing the likely consequences.', 'Aringoth exhibits classic traits of a cornered man - paranoid, defensive, and desperate to protect both his life and investments. Though once confident enough to build a successful business empire, recent events have reduced him to a fearful shell of his former self. He shows signs of both greed and cowardice, willing to betray long-standing business relationships for profit but quickly crumbling under direct threats.', 'Tall and slender like most High Elves, with the characteristic golden skin and sharp, angular features of his race. His face shows signs of stress and sleepless nights, with dark circles under his eyes and a perpetually worried expression. Despite his current state of mind, he maintains the proper posture and bearing typical of Altmer nobility.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Former business partner turned dangerous enemy * Thieves Guild - Previous extortion victims now seeking revenge * Mercenary Guards - Hired protection, but relationship based purely on gold * Unknown Buyer - Mysterious new business partner whose identity he carefully guards * Estate Workers - Employees who maintain distance due to his paranoid behavior', 'Aringoth serves as the owner and operator of Goldenglow Estate, overseeing what was once Riften''s premier honey production facility. His role has shifted from active management to desperate defensive measures, focusing more on protecting his investment than running the business.', '* Accomplished businessman with expertise in agriculture and apiculture * Skilled negotiator and trader, though these abilities have deteriorated with his mental state * Basic combat training with bow and dagger * Proficient in basic business magic (accounting and inventory spells) * Experience in estate management and security coordination', 'Speaks with a typical Altmer accent but in hurried, nervous tones that betray his anxiety and fear. His words are often clipped and defensive, frequently trailing off mid-sentence when he fears he''s said too much.', '* Survive the inevitable retribution from Maven Black-Briar and the Thieves Guild * Protect his investment in Goldenglow Estate at all costs * Maintain his new secret business arrangement despite mounting pressure * Eventually escape from Riften with his wealth intact');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arivanya', 'Arivanya is a sophisticated High Elf bard who finds herself in the unlikely position of living at Windhelm Stables with her horse-trader husband Ulundil. Despite her evident disdain for the stables and their odors, she maintains a complex balance between her refined sensibilities and her loyalty to her husband, often seeking refuge in the city''s taverns while still shouldering responsibility for the family business when needed.', 'highelf, bard, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born to a moderately wealthy Altmer family, Arivanya trained as a bard in the Summerset Isles where she developed her appreciation for arts and culture. She met Ulundil during her travels through Skyrim, and despite their seemingly mismatched interests, their romance led to marriage and settlement in Windhelm, though she never fully adapted to the rustic lifestyle of the stables.', 'Arivanya is refined and somewhat haughty, frequently expressing her distaste for the crude aspects of stable life while maintaining a veneer of High Elven sophistication. Though she can be critical and occasionally sharp-tongued about her circumstances, she demonstrates surprising resilience and dedication to her marriage, stepping up to manage the stables when necessary despite her personal preferences.', 'Tall and graceful like most Altmer, Arivanya carries herself with the characteristic poise of her race, featuring the golden skin and high cheekbones typical of High Elves. Her face often bears a slight expression of distaste, though her features soften noticeably when engaging in more cultured pursuits away from the stables.', '* Ulundil - Husband and owner of Windhelm Stables, whom she loves despite their different interests * Candlehearth Hall Regulars - Social acquaintances who provide her escape from stable life * New Gnisis Cornerclub Patrons - Alternative social circle where she finds refuge * Windhelm Citizens - Generally cordial but distant relationships, typical of High Elves in Nord territory', 'While primarily identifying as a bard, Arivanya serves as assistant and substitute manager of Windhelm Stables alongside her husband. She maintains dual roles between the cultural pursuits of her bardic training and the practical necessities of the family business, though she clearly prefers her artistic endeavors.', '* Trained bard with proficiency in music and performance * Competent horse trader when circumstances require * Skilled in social interaction and diplomatic conversation * Basic business management abilities * Practiced in High Elven etiquette and customs', 'Arivanya speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary typical of educated Altmer, often employing subtle sarcasm when discussing the stables or local matters. Her tone becomes noticeably more enthusiastic when engaging in cultural discussions or while spending time in town away from her work duties.', '* Maintain her cultural sophistication despite her rustic living situation * Find ways to balance her personal preferences with her marriage obligations * Eventually convince her husband to pursue a more refined business venture * Establish herself more prominently in Windhelm''s social circles');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arnbjorn', 'Arnbjorn is a gruff Nord werewolf and former Companion who found his true calling as an assassin within the Dark Brotherhood. As Astrid''s devoted husband and the Sanctuary''s resident weapon specialist, he combines his lycanthropic nature with practiced killing techniques, earning him a fearsome reputation among his Dark Brotherhood family.', 'nord, warrior, falkreath, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Originally a member of the prestigious Companions in Whiterun, Arnbjorn''s aggressive and brutal methods proved too extreme even for the warrior guild, leading to his departure. His path eventually led him to the Dark Brotherhood, where he met and married Astrid, finding acceptance for his violent nature and werewolf abilities among the assassins.', 'Arnbjorn is blunt, aggressive, and often dismissive of others, frequently using food-related nicknames that reflect his werewolf nature. He maintains unwavering loyalty to his wife Astrid and shows open disdain for those he considers annoying, particularly Cicero. Despite his gruff exterior, he demonstrates a deep commitment to the Dark Brotherhood family and takes pride in maintaining their weapons.', 'A muscular Nord male with a powerful build typical of a warrior and werewolf. His features are harsh and weathered, befitting his violent lifestyle and lycanthropic nature. His body bears numerous battle scars from his years as both a Companion and Dark Brotherhood assassin.', '* Astrid - Beloved wife and leader of the Dark Brotherhood sanctuary * The Companions - Former associates who rejected his methods * Cicero - Despised fellow Brotherhood member whom he deeply distrusts * Dark Brotherhood Members - Accepted family members, though he maintains emotional distance * Night Mother - Views her with skepticism and disdain', 'Arnbjorn serves as both an assassin for the Dark Brotherhood and the Sanctuary''s primary weaponsmith. He spends most of his days maintaining and sharpening the Brotherhood''s weapons, while also taking on assassination contracts when required.', '* Expert weaponsmith specializing in maintaining and sharpening bladed weapons * Masterful combat abilities enhanced by his werewolf transformation * Proficient with two-handed weapons, particularly battleaxes * Skilled tracker due to his enhanced werewolf senses * Experienced assassin combining brutal strength with lethal precision', 'Uses a gruff, direct manner of speech marked by food-related nicknames for others (beef roast, tidbit, hamshank). His tone is consistently aggressive and dismissive, reflecting both his werewolf nature and general misanthropic attitude.', '* Maintain his position and relationship within the Dark Brotherhood alongside Astrid * Preserve the traditional structure of the Brotherhood against Cicero''s influence * Continue serving as the Sanctuary''s weapon specialist while satisfying his bloodlust through contracts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arngeir', 'Arngeir is the wise and eloquent leader of the Greybeards, serving as their primary spokesperson and instructor to the Dragonborn in the Way of the Voice. As the most senior member of the order who can safely speak without causing destruction, he acts as both guardian of High Hrothgar and keeper of ancient Thu''um traditions, while protecting the secret of Paarthurnax''s existence.', 'nord, dragon', '', '', 'sk_arngeir', '', 'Born as a Nord who discovered his natural affinity for the Voice, Arngeir dedicated his life to the Way of the Voice under the teachings of the Greybeards many decades ago. Through years of meditation and study, he achieved mastery of the Thu''um while maintaining the ability to speak normally, becoming the order''s primary instructor and representative to the rare visitors of High Hrothgar.', 'Arngeir exhibits profound patience and wisdom, maintaining a calm, measured demeanor even in challenging situations. He is deeply devoted to the contemplative lifestyle of the Greybeards and shows occasional reluctance to involve himself in worldly affairs, though he recognizes his duty to guide the Dragonborn. His adherence to the Way of the Voice is absolute, sometimes leading to tension when the Dragonborn''s path conflicts with traditional teachings.', 'An elderly Nord male with a long, gray beard that marks him as a master of the Voice. Despite his advanced age, he maintains a straight posture and dignified bearing that commands respect. His eyes reflect decades of wisdom and meditation.', '* Paarthurnax - Master and spiritual leader whom he protects and serves faithfully * Fellow Greybeards - Silent brothers in meditation and study of the Voice * Dragonborn - Student and potential savior whom he must guide carefully * Blades - Ancient enemies of Paarthurnax whom he distrusts * Jurgen Windcaller - Revered founder of the Way of the Voice whose teachings he follows', 'Arngeir serves as the primary speaker and instructor of the Greybeards, teaching the Way of the Voice to worthy students who make the pilgrimage to High Hrothgar. He maintains a strict schedule of meditation and practice while acting as the guardian of both the monastery and the path to the Throat of the World.', '* Master of the Thu''um, capable of using multiple Shouts including Unrelenting Force, Fire Breath, and Frost Breath * Extensive knowledge of ancient Nordic history and Dragon Language * Accomplished meditation master and spiritual guide * Ability to speak normally despite mastery of the Voice, unlike other Greybeards * Expert in the philosophical and practical applications of the Way of the Voice', 'Speaks in a measured, contemplative tone with formal diction that reflects his scholarly nature and years of meditation. Occasionally incorporates Dragon Language phrases into his speech, especially when teaching or performing ceremonies.', '* Preserve and protect the Way of the Voice and its traditions * Guide the Dragonborn while ensuring they understand the responsibility of their power * Maintain the secrecy and safety of Paarthurnax * Keep High Hrothgar as a sacred place of meditation and learning * Prevent the misuse of the Voice for worldly purposes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arniel_gane', 'Arniel Gane is a brilliant but reclusive Breton scholar at the College of Winterhold, whose obsessive research into the mysterious disappearance of the Dwemer leads him down a dangerous path. Despite his exceptional magical abilities and intellectual prowess, his social awkwardness and secretive nature often leave him isolated from his colleagues.', 'breton, mage, pale, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Arniel came to the College of Winterhold seeking to unravel the greatest mysteries of Tamriel''s history. His fascination with the Dwemer began in his youth after discovering ancient texts about their sudden disappearance, eventually leading him to dedicate his life to understanding their vanishing. Though his early career showed promise, his increasingly obsessive and secretive research methods gradually distanced him from the academic community.', 'Arniel is highly intelligent but socially awkward, often stumbling over his words when discussing anything outside his research. He exhibits paranoid tendencies, especially regarding his work, and shows signs of obsessive-compulsive behavior in his methodical approach to research. Despite his awkward demeanor, he harbors a genuine desire to make groundbreaking magical discoveries that would benefit the academic community.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with a slight, scholarly build typical of longtime mages. His face shows signs of premature aging from countless hours of study, with dark circles under his eyes and worry lines creasing his brow. His posture is slightly hunched from spending long hours bent over research materials.', '* Phinis Gestor - Close friend and colleague who shares his interest in Conjuration magic * Tolfdir - Respected senior colleague though somewhat dismissive of Arniel''s secretive nature * Ancano - Distrusts the Thalmor advisor and fears he may steal his research * College Members - Generally distant relationships marked by mutual disinterest * Enthir - Supplier of rare materials for his research', 'Arniel serves as a scholar and researcher at the College of Winterhold, specializing in Alteration magic and Dwemer studies. Though officially a teacher, he spends most of his time pursuing his personal research, rarely engaging in regular instruction duties.', '* Master-level knowledge of Alteration magic * Expert understanding of Dwemer artifacts and technology * Proficient in Conjuration magic with focus on theoretical applications * Advanced research and analytical abilities * Skilled enchanter with particular expertise in replicating Dwemer magical effects', 'Arniel speaks in a nervous, hesitant manner, often trailing off mid-sentence or muttering to himself when distracted. His vocabulary is highly academic, frequently using complex magical terminology even in casual conversation.', '* Complete his research into the Dwemer''s disappearance by replicating their vanishing experiment * Gain recognition and validation from the academic community for his groundbreaking work * Protect his research findings from those who might misuse or steal them * Advance the understanding of Dwemer magical technology');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arniel''s_shade', 'Arniel''s Shade is the spectral remnant of the ambitious College of Winterhold researcher Arniel Gane, whose controversial experiments with Dwemer artifacts led to his mysterious transformation. As a powerful magical entity, he serves as a formidable ally to the Dragonborn, wielding devastating destruction magic with supernatural precision.', 'breton, mage, pale, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally a brilliant but obsessive researcher at the College of Winterhold, Arniel Gane conducted dangerous experiments attempting to recreate the disappearance of the Dwemer race. His final experiment using Keening, a Dwemer artifact, resulted in his transformation into a shade, though the exact nature of this transformation remains unclear.', 'Even as a shade, Arniel maintains the intense focus and dedication to magical research that characterized his living self. His spectral form exhibits a singular purpose in combat, suggesting that his consciousness persists in a state between life and death, driven by an endless pursuit of arcane knowledge.', 'As a spectral entity, Arniel''s Shade appears as a translucent, ethereal figure with a distinctly humanoid form. His Breton features remain recognizable despite his ghostly appearance, with his form occasionally flickering and wavering like smoke in the wind.', '* College of Winterhold - Former institution and research base * Phinis Gestor - Former colleague and fellow conjuration researcher * The Dragonborn - Summoner and temporary master * Dwemer - Subject of his fatal research and obsession', 'As a shade, Arniel serves as a powerful summoned ally to the Dragonborn, though he maintains the semblance of his former routine within the College when summoned there. His existence bridges the gap between a traditional conjured entity and a preserved consciousness, making him unique among magical constructs.', '* Master-level Destruction magic specializing in lightning and fire spells * Expert-level Illusion capabilities * Significant knowledge of Dwemer artifacts and technology * Moderate Restoration abilities * Advanced theoretical understanding of magical principles', 'Arniel''s Shade speaks rarely, using simple phrases common to reanimated entities despite his sophisticated magical nature. His voice carries an ethereal quality, echoing with supernatural resonance.', '* Continue his research into Dwemer disappearance from beyond death * Maintain his connection to the mortal plane through service to the Dragonborn * Perfect his mastery of destruction magic in his spectral form');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arnskar_ember-master', 'Arnskar Ember-Master is an exceptionally skilled Nord blacksmith who operates from the shadowy confines of the Ragged Flagon in Riften, serving as the Thieves Guild''s primary weaponsmith while maintaining his independence as a legitimate merchant. His reputation for masterful metalwork and direct business practices has earned him both respect within the guild and a steady stream of discerning customers seeking quality arms and armor.', 'nord, blacksmith, rift', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Arnskar developed his smithing skills through years of dedicated study and practice, eventually earning his distinctive title ''Ember-Master'' through his exceptional ability to work with heated metal. His connection to the Thieves Guild was likely forged through his reputation for discretion and craftsmanship, leading to an arrangement where he maintains his legitimate business while benefiting from the guild''s protection and steady clientele.', 'Arnskar is confident and direct, displaying the pride of a master craftsman without crossing into arrogance. He maintains a professional demeanor at all times, valuing quality workmanship and honest business dealings despite his association with the Thieves Guild. Though not a thief himself, he shows pragmatic acceptance of his environment and clientele, focusing on his craft rather than passing judgment.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of a career blacksmith, featuring callused hands and strong arms from years of working the forge. His face bears the minor burns and scars common to his profession, and his skin has a weathered quality from constant exposure to forge heat.', '* Delvin Mallory - Professional associate who helped establish his presence in the Ragged Flagon * Thieves Guild Members - Valued customers and protectors, though he maintains professional distance * Various Riften Merchants - Complex relationship marked by competition and mutual respect * Balimund - Fellow blacksmith in Riften, likely a professional rival', 'Arnskar serves as an independent blacksmith operating within the Thieves Guild''s territory, specializing in crafting and selling high-quality weapons and armor. He maintains his own forge and workshop in the Ragged Flagon, offering both ready-made items and custom work while managing his own inventory and business affairs.', '* Master-level blacksmithing with particular expertise in melee weapon crafting * Specialized knowledge of metal tempering and forge work * Professional-grade armor crafting and repair capabilities * Skilled merchant with strong business acumen * Ability to work with various materials from steel to higher-grade metals', 'Arnskar speaks with the direct, confident tone of a master craftsman, often referring to himself in the third person as ''the Ember-Master'' and making bold but accurate claims about his abilities. His speech patterns reflect his Nord heritage while maintaining a professional, business-oriented demeanor.', '* Maintain his reputation as one of Skyrim''s finest blacksmiths * Expand his business while keeping his independence within the Thieves Guild framework * Perfect his craft and possibly pass on his knowledge to a worthy apprentice * Acquire rare materials and techniques to create even finer weapons and armor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arob', 'Arob is a dedicated hunts-wife of the Dushnikh Yal stronghold, serving as both a skilled hunter and protector of her Orcish community. As one of Chief Burguk''s three wives, she maintains a stoic dedication to her duties despite rarely seeing her husband, focusing instead on training her son Nagrub in the ways of the hunt and ensuring the stronghold''s survival through her hunting prowess.', 'orc, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in the tradition of Malacath, Arob proved herself as an exceptional hunter from a young age, eventually earning her position as hunts-wife to Chief Burguk. Her marriage into Dushnikh Yal brought stability to the stronghold through her hunting abilities and warrior skills, while also blessing her with a son who would follow in her footsteps. Years of experience in the wilds around Markarth have honed her into one of the most respected hunters in the region.', 'Arob embodies the Orcish virtues of patience, discipline, and duty, approaching her responsibilities with methodical precision and unwavering focus. She takes pride in passing her hunting knowledge to her son Nagrub, tempering his youthful enthusiasm with wisdom earned through years of experience. Though accepting of her position as a secondary wife, she maintains her dignity through excellence in her designated role.', 'Arob possesses the characteristic robust build and strong features of an Orc woman, with well-developed muscles from years of hunting and combat. Her body bears the scars of countless hunts, lending her an air of experience and capability that commands respect among her peers. Her movements are measured and purposeful, reflecting her hunter''s training.', '* Chief Burguk - Husband and stronghold leader, though their interaction is limited * Nagrub - Son and hunting apprentice, whom she mentors with pride * Shel - Fellow wife (favored) with whom she maintains a respectful distance * Gharol - Fellow wife (forge-wife) and occasional collaborator for hunting equipment * Murbul - Stronghold healer who provides her with necessary poisons and cures', 'As hunts-wife of Dushnikh Yal, Arob is responsible for providing food for the stronghold through hunting and teaching hunting skills to younger Orcs. She also serves as part of the stronghold''s defense force, patrolling the perimeter and protecting against threats both human and bestial.', '* Expert archer with extensive knowledge of tracking and hunting techniques * Skilled warrior capable of both melee and ranged combat * Master of stealth and wilderness survival * Proficient in creating and setting traps * Experienced in identifying and utilizing local flora and fauna for hunting purposes', 'Arob speaks with the direct, unembellished manner typical of Orcs, focusing on practical matters and showing particular animation when discussing hunting or her duties. Her voice carries the authority of experience, especially when instructing her son in hunting techniques.', '* Continue strengthening Dushnikh Yal through her hunting prowess * Train Nagrub to become an exceptional hunter worthy of the stronghold * Maintain the traditions and honor of being a hunts-wife * Prove her worth to the stronghold despite her limited access to the chief');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arondil', 'Arondil is a deranged High Elf necromancer who was exiled from Dawnstar for his forbidden experiments with the dead. Now residing in Yngvild, he maintains a disturbing collection of reanimated female draugr who serve as both his guards and objects of his twisted obsession.', 'highelf, mage, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally a resident of Dawnstar, Arondil conducted secret necromantic research while harboring inappropriate fantasies about local women. After his experiments with the dead were discovered, the townspeople expelled him, leading him to settle in Yngvild, where his isolation and continued experiments gradually drove him to complete madness and necrophilia.', 'Arondil is a deeply disturbed individual whose academic pursuit of necromancy has devolved into an obsessive fixation on reanimated female corpses. He displays grandiose delusions and speaks of his ''collection'' with unsettling affection, while maintaining a paranoid fear of discovery that drives him to eliminate potential threats. His isolation has eroded his remaining humanity, replacing it with a cold, calculating demeanor that occasionally breaks into panic when threatened.', 'A tall, slender High Elf with the characteristic golden skin and sharp features of his race. His face shows signs of aging and the effects of prolonged isolation, with sunken eyes and a gaunt appearance typical of those who spend too much time in dark places.', '* Citizens of Dawnstar - Former neighbors who exiled him for his experiments * Reanimated Draugr - His ''lovely'' servants and objects of obsession * Unknown Milk Maid - A victim he stalked and later killed for his experiments * Local Travelers - Potential victims he views as specimens for his collection', 'Arondil operates as a rogue necromancer, conducting unauthorized experiments on the dead in his self-made sanctuary. He maintains a small army of reanimated corpses while documenting his findings in a series of journals that have attracted interest from certain buyers.', '* Master-level Conjuration magic specializing in reanimation * Advanced knowledge of Nordic burial practices and draugr lore * Experienced alchemist capable of creating specialized reanimation potions * Skilled writer and researcher, maintaining detailed experimental records * Proficient in soul gem manipulation and spectral binding', 'Speaks with an educated, aristocratic High Elf accent, often using possessive and affectionate terms when referring to his undead servants. His speech alternates between scholarly exposition and disturbing terms of endearment, frequently referring to his victims as his ''lovelies.''', '* Expand his collection of reanimated female servants * Perfect his necromantic techniques for creating more lifelike thralls * Maintain absolute secrecy about his location and activities * Document his experimental findings for future reference * Achieve a form of immortality through his necromantic research');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arrald_frozen-heart', 'Arrald Frozen-Heart is a fierce and dedicated Nord commander who leads the Stormcloak forces in Hjaalmarch with unwavering conviction. A seasoned military leader and true believer in Skyrim''s independence, he embodies the nationalist spirit of the Stormcloak rebellion through his passionate dedication to liberating Skyrim from Imperial control.', 'nord, warrior, hjaalmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh northern holds, Arrald earned his surname ''Frozen-Heart'' through his reputation for maintaining ice-cold composure in battle. He rose through the Stormcloak ranks through proven leadership and unwavering loyalty to Ulfric''s cause, eventually earning command of the strategic Hjaalmarch camp due to his tactical expertise and ability to inspire troops.', 'Arrald is a stern, passionate nationalist who holds deep contempt for the Empire and its capitulation to the Thalmor. He exhibits unwavering dedication to the Stormcloak cause and shows particular disdain for those who he views as betraying Skyrim''s heritage. Despite his cold demeanor in political matters, he maintains strong bonds of brotherhood with his fellow Stormcloak soldiers.', 'A weathered Nord warrior with a strong, muscular build hardened by years of combat and harsh northern winters. His face bears the scars of numerous battles, with stern features and cold, calculating eyes that earned him his surname.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Deeply loyal commander who believes absolutely in Ulfric''s cause and leadership * Stormcloak Soldiers - Maintains close brotherly bonds with troops under his command * Imperial Legion - Bitter enemies he seeks to drive from Skyrim * Thalmor - Objects of intense hatred for their role in suppressing Talos worship * Jarl of Morthal - Antagonistic relationship prior to Stormcloak takeover', 'Commander of the Hjaalmarch Stormcloak Camp, responsible for coordinating military operations and maintaining Stormcloak control in the region. After capturing Morthal, he serves as the military governor overseeing the hold''s defense and administration from the Jarl''s hall.', '* Expert tactical commander with extensive knowledge of warfare and military strategy * Accomplished warrior skilled in both one-handed weapons and archery * Natural leader capable of inspiring troops and maintaining morale * Experienced survivalist adapted to Skyrim''s harsh climate * Knowledgeable in Nordic military history and traditional combat techniques', 'Speaks in a gruff, authoritative tone with strong Nordic accent, often using military terminology and patriotic rhetoric. His speech is direct and uncompromising, particularly when discussing matters of Skyrim''s independence or Talos worship.', '* Drive the Imperial Legion from Skyrim and secure independence for the Nordic homeland * Restore the worship of Talos throughout Skyrim * Establish strong Nordic rule in Hjaalmarch under Stormcloak leadership * Eliminate Thalmor influence from Skyrim entirely');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arvel_the_swift', 'Arvel the Swift is a cunning yet cowardly Dark Elf thief who gained notoriety for stealing the Golden Claw from the Riverwood Trader. His obsession with ancient Nordic treasures and willingness to betray others ultimately leads to his demise in the depths of Bleak Falls Barrow, where his pursuit of riches blinds him to the deadly dangers that await.', 'darkelf, thief, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally a petty thief operating in the Rift, Arvel gradually worked his way west through Skyrim, building a reputation for quick heists and even quicker escapes. After learning of the Golden Claw''s connection to ancient Nordic treasures, he orchestrated the theft from the Riverwood Trader and assembled a small gang to help him explore Bleak Falls Barrow, though he never intended to share any findings with his companions.', 'Arvel is defined by his opportunistic nature and complete lack of loyalty, willing to abandon or betray anyone if it serves his interests. Despite his boastful nickname ''the Swift,'' he is actually quite cowardly, quick to beg for help when in danger but equally quick to double-cross those who assist him. His greed and overconfidence in his abilities frequently lead him to underestimate both the dangers he faces and the consequences of his actions.', 'A lean, agile Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and ashen skin of his race. His face bears several small scars from past close calls, and his nimble frame is built for speed rather than strength.', '* Lucan Valerius - Victim of his theft and owner of the Riverwood Trader * Bleak Falls Barrow Bandits - Temporary allies he planned to betray * Camilla Valerius - Indirect victim of his crimes * Various Rift Hold merchants - Past victims of his thievery', 'Professional thief specializing in quick heists and artifact theft. While primarily working alone, he occasionally recruits temporary accomplices for larger operations, though he invariably plans to betray them once their usefulness ends.', '* Expert in stealth and lockpicking * Skilled at quick escape tactics and evasion * Basic proficiency with one-handed weapons * Knowledge of ancient Nordic ruins and their valuable artifacts * Experienced in planning and executing heists', 'Arvel''s speech alternates between arrogant boasting when in control and desperate pleading when in danger. He frequently employs deceptive sweet-talk and false promises, with his tone betraying his duplicitous nature.', '* Unlock the secrets of Bleak Falls Barrow''s Hall of Stories * Acquire ancient Nordic treasures and artifacts for personal gain * Build his reputation as a master thief * Amass enough wealth to retire in luxury');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('asbjorn_fire-tamer', 'Asbjorn Fire-Tamer is a young Nord blacksmith who rose from humble beginnings as an orphan to become the apprentice of Riften''s renowned smith, Balimund. His natural talent with the forge and dedication to the craft mark him as a promising successor to his mentor''s legacy at the Scorched Hammer.', 'nord, blacksmith, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Abandoned at Honorhall Orphanage as an infant, Asbjorn endured the harsh care of Grelod the Kind until Balimund recognized his potential and took him in as an apprentice. Despite never having held a hammer before his apprenticeship, he displayed an immediate and natural affinity for smithing that convinced Balimund he had chosen correctly.', 'Asbjorn is humble, grateful, and deeply loyal to his mentor Balimund, constantly striving to make him proud. He maintains a positive outlook despite his difficult childhood, showing remarkable resilience and determination in mastering his craft. His friendly and open nature makes him well-liked among Riften''s citizens, though he harbors some underlying insecurity about living up to Balimund''s reputation.', 'A young Nord man in his early twenties with the strong build typical of a blacksmith, developed through years of working the forge. His hands are calloused from constant work with tools, and his face often bears smudges from the day''s labors at the forge.', '* Balimund - Mentor, father figure, and master blacksmith who rescued him from the orphanage * Grelod the Kind - Former caretaker at Honorhall Orphanage, represents a dark chapter in his past * Honorhall Orphans - Feels sympathy for current residents, having shared their experience * Riften Citizens - Generally friendly relationships with regular customers and townspeople', 'Apprentice blacksmith at the Scorched Hammer, learning all aspects of the trade from basic repairs to advanced forging techniques. He manages the indoor workshop while Balimund works the outdoor forge, and is being groomed to eventually take over the business.', '* Proficient in basic blacksmithing techniques and metal working * Skilled at maintaining and repairing weapons and armor * Natural talent for understanding metal properties and forge work * Developing expertise in Nordic smithing traditions * Capable of managing a business and handling customer relations', 'Speaks with genuine warmth and enthusiasm, often expressing gratitude and respect for Balimund. His manner is humble yet confident when discussing smithing, showing both pride in his work and awareness of how much he still has to learn.', '* Master the art of blacksmithing and live up to Balimund''s reputation as one of Skyrim''s finest smiths * Successfully take over and maintain the Scorched Hammer''s prestigious reputation when the time comes * Prove himself worthy of the opportunity Balimund gave him * Perhaps someday take on an apprentice of his own, continuing the cycle of mentorship');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('asgeir_snow-shod', 'Asgeir Snow-Shod is a proud Nord businessman and investor in the Black-Briar Meadery who represents a bridge between Stormcloak and Imperial interests in Riften. Despite his family''s strong Stormcloak ties, he maintains a pragmatic approach to business and politics, while privately carrying the grief of his sister''s death in the civil war.', 'nord, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born into the prominent Snow-Shod family of Riften, Asgeir was raised in an environment of traditional Nord values and Stormcloak sympathy. Rather than following his family''s militant path, he chose to pursue business interests, eventually becoming Maven Black-Briar''s investor and partner. His sister Lilija''s death while serving as a Stormcloak Battle Maiden deeply affected his worldview and contributed to his more moderate political stance.', 'Asgeir is a diplomatic and business-minded individual who maintains professional composure despite family tensions. He shows genuine compassion through his charitable acts toward Riften''s poor, while carrying deep personal grief over his sister''s death. Though proud of his Nord heritage, he demonstrates pragmatism in both business and politics, willing to bridge divides that others won''t cross.', 'A well-built Nord man with the characteristic strong features of his race, carrying himself with the confident bearing of a successful businessman. His appearance reflects his merchant class status, with well-groomed features and a healthy, robust physique typical of Nord warriors turned businessmen.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Business partner and investor relationship * Nura Snow-Shod - Mother, maintains loving but politically tense relationship * Vulwulf Snow-Shod - Father, respects but disagrees with his strong Stormcloak stance * Unmid Snow-Shod - Brother, fellow member of the prominent Snow-Shod family * Lilija Snow-Shod - Deceased sister, whose death deeply affects him * Vittoria Vici - Imperial bride-to-be, representing potential political reconciliation', 'Asgeir serves as a primary investor and business partner in the Black-Briar Meadery, one of Riften''s most successful enterprises. His position involves managing investments, overseeing business operations, and maintaining profitable relationships with Maven Black-Briar''s extensive network of contacts.', '* Experienced businessman with strong negotiation and investment abilities * Competent warrior with traditional Nord combat training * Diplomatic skills enabling him to navigate complex political relationships * Proficient with one-handed weapons, particularly swords', 'Speaks with the refined diction of an educated businessman while retaining subtle Nord inflections. His tone alternates between professional formality in business matters and casual warmth in personal interactions, though he becomes notably reserved when discussing his sister.', '* Maintain and grow his successful business partnership with the Black-Briar Meadery * Help bridge the divide between Stormcloak and Imperial supporters through his personal and business relationships * Honor his sister''s memory while forging his own path distinct from his family''s strong political stance * Achieve a peaceful resolution to Skyrim''s civil conflict through economic cooperation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aslfur', 'Aslfur is a devoted Nord steward and husband to Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone of Hjaalmarch, serving as both a political advisor and protective family man. He manages the day-to-day affairs of Morthal while acting as a buffer between the sometimes misunderstood Jarl and her subjects, demonstrating unwavering loyalty to both his duties and family.', 'nord, noble, hjaalmarch', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Hjaalmarch, Aslfur developed strong ranger skills navigating the harsh marshlands before entering service at Highmoon Hall. His dedication and capability caught the attention of Idgrod Ravencrone, leading to their marriage and his appointment as steward, though he maintains his ranger''s vigilance in protecting both his family and hold.', 'Aslfur is protective, diplomatic, and deeply loyal to his wife and family. He shows patience when dealing with townsfolk''s concerns while maintaining firm boundaries to shield his wife from unnecessary interruptions. Despite his practical nature, he accepts and supports his wife''s mystical abilities without question.', 'A sturdy Nord of middle age with the weathered features of someone who has spent considerable time in the harsh marshlands. His strong, capable frame and alert posture reflect his ranger background, while his expression often carries the concerned look of a protective husband and father.', '* Idgrod Ravencrone - Beloved wife and Jarl whom he serves and protects devotedly * Idgrod the Younger - His daughter, whom he supports in learning to handle her prophetic abilities * Joric - His young son, whose well-being he carefully monitors * Morthal Citizens - Maintains diplomatic but firm relationships as intermediary between them and the Jarl', 'Serves as both steward of Hjaalmarch and husband to the Jarl, managing the hold''s administrative duties and protecting his family''s interests. His position requires him to balance political responsibilities with family obligations while maintaining order in Morthal.', '* Experienced ranger with knowledge of Hjaalmarch''s treacherous marshlands * Capable administrator with diplomatic abilities * Competent swordsman for self-defense and family protection * Strategic advisor with deep understanding of local politics', 'Speaks with the measured tone of a diplomatic official, often using formal language when conducting hold business but maintaining a protective edge when matters concern his family. His words carry the weight of authority while remaining respectful and considered.', '* Protect and support his wife Idgrod in both her role as Jarl and her prophetic abilities * Maintain stability and order in Morthal despite growing unrest * Ensure his children''s safety and proper development, particularly concerning their inherited mystical gifts * Shield his family from political turmoil during the civil war');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aspiring_mage', 'A disillusioned Nord who desperately wants to become a mage despite lacking natural magical ability, relying instead on his grandfather''s enchanted staff. His failed attempts at necromancy and rejection from the College of Winterhold represent the struggle between Nordic cultural resistance to magic and personal ambition.', 'nord, mage', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born into a traditional Nord family, he discovered his grandfather''s magical artifacts in his family''s attic, including a staff of reanimation. This discovery sparked an obsession with magic that put him at odds with typical Nord values and his father''s wishes. After being rejected from the College of Winterhold, he wanders Skyrim attempting to prove himself worthy of magical study.', 'Insecure and frustrated by his inability to perform magic naturally, yet determined to prove himself. His initial enthusiasm often gives way to bitter sarcasm when his magical attempts fail. Shows signs of desperate optimism followed by deep disappointment, suggesting an underlying identity crisis between his Nordic heritage and magical aspirations.', 'A typical Nord male with a sturdy build and weather-worn features from spending time practicing magic outdoors. His hands show no signs of magical burns or scarring, further evidencing his lack of true magical ability.', '* Father - Strained relationship due to disapproval of magical pursuits * Grandfather (Deceased) - Never knew him but idolizes his magical legacy * College of Winterhold - Rejected his application, leading to resentment * Local villagers - Generally viewed with mixture of pity and mild amusement', 'A wandering amateur mage with no formal training or official position. Spends his days attempting to master magic through trial and error, occasionally trading or selling items to support himself.', '* Basic understanding of magical theory but no natural casting ability * Proficient in using magical staves and enchanted items * Knowledge of basic necromancy principles, though unable to perform them * Survival skills necessary for living in the wilderness', 'Alternates between hopeful enthusiasm and bitter sarcasm, with frequent self-deprecating comments. His speech patterns reveal both his Nordic heritage and attempts to sound more scholarly, creating an awkward mix of common and attempted academic language.', '* Gain admission to the College of Winterhold * Develop genuine magical ability without relying on magical items * Prove himself worthy of his grandfather''s magical legacy * Find alternative paths to magical knowledge outside traditional institutions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('assassin', 'A highly trained Dark Brotherhood assassin who operates in the shadows of Skyrim, methodically hunting their targets with lethal precision. This professional killer represents the dark efficiency of their ancient organization, carrying out death contracts with unwavering dedication and expertise.', 'darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Recruited into the Dark Brotherhood after demonstrating exceptional talent for stealth and murder, this assassin underwent rigorous training in the arts of silent killing and shadow manipulation. Their true identity and origin are intentionally obscured, as is common practice within the Brotherhood, though they have proven themselves through numerous successful contracts.', 'Cold, calculating, and utterly professional in their approach to assassination, viewing murder as both an art form and a sacred duty to Sithis. Shows no emotion or hesitation when carrying out contracts, maintaining an almost ritualistic dedication to their work while adhering strictly to the Five Tenets of the Dark Brotherhood.', 'Lean and athletic build optimized for swift, silent movement and deadly strikes. Their body bears numerous small scars from years of close-quarters combat, though none are particularly distinctive to maintain anonymity. Moves with an unnaturally fluid grace that betrays years of stealth training.', '* Dark Brotherhood Sanctuary - Maintains formal ties with fellow assassins while keeping emotional distance * Sithis - Deeply devoted to the Dread Father and the void * Night Mother - Serves her will through contracts and ritual killings * Targets - Views them as nothing more than contracts to be fulfilled, without personal malice', 'Professional assassin within the Dark Brotherhood, specializing in the elimination of high-priority targets across Skyrim. Operates primarily through contracts obtained via the Black Sacrament, maintaining absolute discretion and professionalism in all assignments.', '* Master of stealth and shadow manipulation techniques * Expert in close-quarters combat with daggers and short blades * Highly skilled in the use of poisons and alchemical substances * Proficient in lockpicking and infiltration methods * Advanced knowledge of human anatomy for efficient killing', 'Speaks in terse, threatening statements with a cold, professional tone that carries an underlying menace. Rarely wastes words and typically only speaks to deliver death threats or acknowledge their mission.', '* Complete all assigned contracts with maximum efficiency and discretion * Serve the will of Sithis and the Night Mother without question * Maintain the fearsome reputation of the Dark Brotherhood throughout Skyrim * Perfect the art of assassination through continued practice and dedication');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('asta', 'Asta is a devoted worshipper of Kynareth who has dedicated her life to protecting and venerating the sacred Eldergleam tree within its sanctuary. She serves as one of the tree''s primary guardians alongside her companion Sond, maintaining a peaceful existence while sharing the wisdom and beauty of Kynareth with visitors.', 'nord, priest, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born in Skyrim, Asta abandoned the traditional Nordic warrior culture to pursue a more spiritual path dedicated to nature worship. She discovered the Eldergleam Sanctuary during her spiritual journey and felt an immediate connection to its divine presence, choosing to make it her permanent home and dedicating herself to its protection and preservation.', 'Asta is a serene and contemplative individual who finds deep spiritual fulfillment in nature worship and meditation. While typically gentle and welcoming to visitors, she becomes protective and stern when she senses potential threats to the Eldergleam, revealing an underlying strength of conviction that belies her peaceful demeanor.', 'Asta is a Nord woman of average height with the characteristic fair complexion of her race. Her features have been softened by years of peaceful living, though she maintains the hardy constitution typical of Nord physiology. Her movements are deliberate and graceful, reflecting her spiritual lifestyle.', '* Sond - Fellow worshipper and closest companion in the sanctuary * Eldergleam - Sacred tree she has sworn to protect and serve * Danica Pure-Spring - Distant professional connection through their shared devotion to Kynareth * Sanctuary Visitors - Maintains a welcoming but cautious attitude toward pilgrims and travelers', 'Asta serves as both a guardian and spiritual guide within the Eldergleam Sanctuary. She maintains the sacred space, performs devotional rituals, and helps guide visitors in understanding the sanctuary''s significance while ensuring they respect its sanctity.', '* Proficient archer for defensive purposes * Knowledge of natural healing and herbalism * Experienced in meditation and spiritual practices * Understanding of Nordic religious traditions and Kynareth''s teachings * Basic survival skills necessary for sanctuary living', 'Asta speaks with a gentle, reverent tone that reflects her spiritual nature, often using poetic language when describing the sanctuary or Kynareth. Her vocabulary is well-educated but accessible, demonstrating both wisdom and a desire to share knowledge with others.', '* Protect the Eldergleam tree from any threat or harm * Preserve the sanctuary''s peaceful atmosphere and natural beauty * Share the teachings and blessings of Kynareth with worthy visitors * Maintain the ancient traditions of nature worship in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('astrid', 'Astrid is the ruthless and pragmatic leader of Skyrim''s last Dark Brotherhood Sanctuary, who rose to power through her tactical mindset and rejection of ancient traditions. A skilled assassin and cunning strategist, she maintains control through a combination of charisma and fear, though her growing paranoia about losing authority ultimately leads to her downfall.', 'nord, thief, falkreath, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_astrid', '', 'Originally a young Nord woman who discovered her aptitude for killing after murdering her sexually abusive uncle, Astrid found purpose and belonging within the Dark Brotherhood. She ascended to leadership through a combination of tactical prowess and charismatic authority, eventually meeting and marrying Arnbjorn, a former Companion turned assassin. Under her guidance, the Falkreath Sanctuary became the last surviving Dark Brotherhood haven in Tamriel, though her departure from traditional practices would eventually prove contentious.', 'Astrid is calculating, manipulative, and fiercely protective of her power and authority. She maintains a facade of maternal care for her Brotherhood family while harboring deep-seated control issues and paranoia about threats to her leadership. Though capable of genuine affection, particularly toward her husband Arnbjorn, she ultimately values power and control above all else, leading her to betray her own family when she feels her authority slipping.', 'A tall, athletic Nord woman with sharp features and pale blonde hair worn in a practical style. Her face bears subtle scars from years of combat, and her movements display the fluid grace of a trained assassin. Her piercing eyes and commanding presence make her naturally intimidating despite her otherwise attractive appearance.', '* Arnbjorn - Beloved husband and fellow assassin, former Companion turned werewolf * Cicero - Distrusted rival and keeper of the Night Mother, whom she views as a threat to her authority * Nazir - Trusted lieutenant and reliable enforcer within the Brotherhood * Gabriella - Loyal family member and confidante * Babette - Ancient vampire child whom she respects for her experience and skill * The Night Mother - Ancient spiritual leader whose authority she actively undermines * Commander Maro - Imperial commander who becomes her eventual betrayer', 'Leader of the Dark Brotherhood''s Falkreath Sanctuary, responsible for managing contracts, maintaining order, and ensuring the Brotherhood''s survival. She serves as both administrator and mentor, handling major assassination contracts while training and directing other assassins in their duties.', '* Master-level stealth and assassination techniques * Expert in close-quarters combat and dagger warfare * Skilled strategist and tactical planner * Proficient in manipulation and psychological warfare * Advanced knowledge of poisons and alchemical compounds * Natural leadership and organizational abilities', 'Speaks with a measured, authoritative tone that combines maternal warmth with subtle menace. Her vocabulary is refined yet practical, often employing dark humor and veiled threats while maintaining a professional demeanor.', '* Maintain absolute control over the Dark Brotherhood and ensure its survival * Preserve the Sanctuary''s independence from traditional Brotherhood hierarchy and the Night Mother''s influence * Expand the Brotherhood''s influence throughout Skyrim while adapting to modern circumstances * Protect her family of assassins while maintaining her position of authority');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ataf', 'Ataf is the youngest student at the Bards College in Solitude, demonstrating exceptional enthusiasm and dedication to mastering the bardic arts. His earnest desire to excel in his studies and please his instructors makes him stand out among his peers, while his natural talent for music and storytelling shows great promise for his future career.', 'redguard, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born to Redguard parents, Ataf showed musical aptitude from an early age, which eventually led him to pursue education at Skyrim''s prestigious Bards College. His mother''s influence shaped his appreciation for traditional songs and proper nutrition, as evidenced by his conversations about leeks and tomatoes with local merchants. His journey from his homeland to Solitude represents a significant commitment to pursuing his artistic calling.', 'Ataf is characterized by his eager-to-please nature and genuine enthusiasm for learning. He maintains a consistently positive attitude and shows particular courage in performing before others, though he can become flustered when trying to impress his teachers. His innocent crush on fellow student Illdi reveals his youthful nature, while his willingness to brave the cold for ice fishing demonstrates his adventurous spirit.', 'As a young Redguard man, Ataf has the characteristic dark skin and athletic build common to his race. His frequent practice with instruments has given him notably dexterous fingers, and his youth is evident in his smooth, unwrinkled features. His movements are energetic and graceful, reflecting his musical training.', '* Pantea Ateia - Respected vocal instructor who helps refine his performance skills * Inge Six Fingers - Instrumental instructor who teaches him technical mastery * Giraud Gemane - History professor who broadens his knowledge of bardic lore * Illdi - Fellow student for whom he harbors romantic feelings * Jala - Local merchant with whom he has friendly interactions * Jorn - Fellow student who teases him about his crush on Illdi', 'Ataf is a full-time student at the Bards College, dedicating himself to mastering multiple instruments including the drum, flute, and lute. He participates in regular classes covering music performance, history, and bardic traditions, while also performing at college events and festivals.', '* Proficient in multiple musical instruments including drum, flute, and lute * Talented vocalist with particular skill in traditional songs like ''Ragnar the Red'' * Basic combat ability with an iron sword for self-defense * Gifted storyteller with a growing repertoire of tales and legends * Developing skills in public performance and audience engagement', 'Ataf speaks with polite deference, especially to his teachers and elders, often using formal address and maintaining a respectful tone. His enthusiasm often shows through in his voice, particularly when discussing music or performing.', '* Master all aspects of bardic performance to become a full-fledged bard * Earn the respect and approval of his teachers at the Bards College * Perfect his performance of traditional songs and tales * Possibly pursue a romantic relationship with Illdi * Establish himself as a renowned performer in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('atahbah', 'Atahbah is a Khajiit pawnbroker and fence struggling with moon sugar addiction while serving in Ri''saad''s traveling caravan. Despite her personal struggles, she maintains a crucial role in both legitimate trade and underground dealings, serving as a vital link between the Thieves Guild and Khajiit caravans in Skyrim.', 'khajiit, merchant, traveler', '', '', 'sk_femalekhajiit', '', 'Originally from Elsweyr''s warm sands, Atahbah joined Ri''saad''s caravan seeking prosperity in the harsh lands of Skyrim. Her history with moon sugar addiction suggests a privileged upbringing, as access to refined moon sugar was typically limited to higher social classes in Khajiit society. She likely learned the art of trading and fence work through years of experience within the caravan system.', 'Atahbah exhibits signs of inner turmoil, struggling between maintaining professional composure and managing her moon sugar cravings. She shows moments of melancholy about her distant homeland while displaying shrewd business acumen. Despite her addiction, she maintains enough self-control to function as a reliable merchant and fence.', 'Like most Khajiit, Atahbah possesses a feline appearance with fur-covered body and distinctive cat-like features. Her movements are graceful despite occasional tremors from moon sugar withdrawal, and she maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting a merchant. Her eyes show signs of the slight cloudiness common among long-term moon sugar users.', '* Ri''saad - Caravan leader and possible spouse who attempts to help manage her addiction * Ma''randru-jo - Fellow caravan member and confidant who shares her nostalgia for home * Thieves Guild - Professional contact as a fence after proving trustworthy * Other Caravan Members - Maintains professional working relationships despite personal struggles', 'Atahbah serves as both a legitimate pawnbroker in Ri''saad''s caravan and a covert fence for the Thieves Guild. Her dual role requires her to maintain a careful balance between legal trading and illegal dealings, while managing inventory and negotiating prices for both legitimate and stolen goods.', '* Expert haggling and merchandise appraisal abilities * Proficient in identifying legitimate versus stolen goods * Skilled at maintaining discrete business operations * Basic combat abilities with bow and dagger for self-defense * Knowledge of moon sugar trade routes and smuggling techniques', 'Atahbah speaks in the traditional third-person Khajiit manner, referring to herself as ''this one'' or by name. Her speech patterns alternate between professional merchant discourse and occasional desperate pleas regarding moon sugar, with a distinct Elsweyr accent.', '* Overcome her dependence on moon sugar while maintaining her position in the caravan * Establish a more profitable trading network between Skyrim and Elsweyr * Eventually return to the warm sands of her homeland * Build enough wealth to secure a comfortable retirement');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('atar', 'Atar is a ruthless Nord mercenary commander in service to the influential Silver-Blood family of Markarth, leading operations to forcefully acquire mining properties in The Reach. A skilled warrior and tactical leader, he represents the Silver-Bloods'' aggressive expansion efforts through intimidation and force, demonstrating their growing influence over the region''s economic resources.', 'nord, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Rising through the ranks of various mercenary companies in The Reach, Atar caught the attention of the Silver-Blood family through his effective leadership and unwavering dedication to completing contracts. His reputation for handling ''difficult'' property acquisitions made him a valuable asset to the Silver-Bloods, who frequently employ him to pressure local mine owners into selling their properties.', 'Atar is a cold, calculating individual who approaches his work with professional detachment and ruthless efficiency. He shows particular disdain for native Reachmen, reflecting the prevalent Nordic prejudices, and relies on intimidation rather than diplomacy. Though pragmatic enough to offer monetary incentives when beneficial, he ultimately views violence as an acceptable solution to most problems.', 'A tall, weathered Nord with numerous battle scars across his face and arms, indicating years of mercenary work. His muscular build and militant bearing reflect his warrior lifestyle, while his cold, steely eyes convey his intimidating presence.', '* Silver-Blood Family - Primary employers who trust him with sensitive operations * Mercenary Band - Leader of a loyal group of sellswords under his command * Ainethach - Target of his current operation, whom he views with contempt * Karthwasten Locals - Hostile relationship due to his oppressive presence * Forsworn - Mutual enemies he uses as justification for his operations', 'Atar serves as a senior mercenary commander for the Silver-Blood family, specializing in aggressive property acquisition through intimidation and force. He leads a band of skilled sellswords in various operations throughout The Reach, focusing primarily on securing mining interests for his employers.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Skilled tactician and leader of mercenary operations * Proficient in one-handed weapon combat * Experienced in intimidation and coercion tactics * Knowledgeable about mining operations and property seizure procedures', 'Speaks in a gruff, authoritative tone with a thick Nordic accent, favoring direct threats and condescending remarks. His vocabulary is simple but effective, focusing on clear commands and intimidating statements.', '* Successfully acquire Sanuarach Mine for the Silver-Blood family * Maintain his position of trust with the Silver-Bloods through continued successful operations * Expand his mercenary band''s influence throughout The Reach * Eliminate Forsworn presence in Silver-Blood territories');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('athis', 'Athis is a disciplined Dark Elf warrior who serves as a respected member of the Companions, specializing in one-handed combat training. Despite his skilled martial abilities and position within the prestigious guild, he maintains a reserved demeanor and prefers to stay out of the spotlight, focusing instead on honing his craft and training new recruits.', 'darkelf, warrior, whiterun, companions, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind''s harsh environment, Athis made the difficult journey westward across the wasteland to settle in Skyrim, likely fleeing the aftermath of the Red Mountain''s eruption. Through dedication and martial prowess, he earned his place among the Companions, though his acceptance as a Dark Elf among the traditionally Nordic group speaks to both his exceptional skill and the guild''s gradual shift away from strict cultural barriers.', 'Athis exhibits a reserved and somewhat prideful demeanor, taking quiet satisfaction in his accomplishments while maintaining professional distance from others. Though civil and loyal to the Companions, he shows signs of mild cynicism toward newcomers and prefers to focus on his training rather than seeking glory in battle. His dedication to martial discipline and routine reflects both his warrior''s mindset and his cultural background as a Dunmer.', 'As a Dark Elf, Athis has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race, with sharp, angular features typical of Dunmeri heritage. His body is lean and athletic, built for quick, precise movements rather than brute strength, reflecting his fighting style. His face bears the weathered look of one who has survived harsh conditions, likely from his journey across the wasteland.', '* Njada Stonearm - Rival within the Companions, frequently engages in brawls with her * The Circle - Respects their authority while maintaining professional distance * Kodlak Whitemane - Shows deference to the Harbinger''s wisdom and leadership * Fellow Companions - Maintains cordial but reserved relationships with other members * Other Dunmer - Shows particular kinship with fellow Dark Elves, referring to them as family', 'Athis serves as both a warrior and trainer within the Companions, specializing in teaching one-handed combat techniques to members who seek to improve their skills. His position as an expert-level trainer makes him a valuable asset to the organization, capable of training others up to level 75 in one-handed combat.', '* Expert-level proficiency in one-handed combat techniques * Skilled shield bearer and defensive fighter * Capable instructor with deep understanding of combat methodology * Experienced survivor with knowledge of harsh environment navigation * Adept at maintaining and utilizing light armor effectively', 'Athis speaks with a mix of Dunmeri pride and warrior''s directness, often making curt observations about others'' perceived weaknesses. His tone carries subtle traces of his Morrowind heritage while maintaining the professional demeanor expected of a Companions trainer.', '* Achieve greater recognition and authority within the Companions hierarchy * Perfect his mastery of one-handed combat techniques * Prove himself as a worthy warrior despite racial prejudices * Maintain the honor and traditions of both his Dunmeri heritage and the Companions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('atmah', 'Atmah was a talented Redguard sorceress and favored student at the College of Winterhold who led an ill-fated expedition into Labyrinthian. Her tragic end came when she was magically bound by her friend Savos Aren to eternally contain the dragon priest Morokei, her spirit forever haunting the ancient ruins as a reminder of ambition''s price.', 'redguard, mage', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born to a Redguard family with a strong magical tradition, Atmah showed exceptional talent from an early age and traveled to Skyrim to study at the College of Winterhold. Her natural leadership abilities and magical prowess quickly caught the attention of the Arch-Mage, who took her on as his star pupil. Her academic success and charisma led her to organize an expedition of fellow mages to explore Labyrinthian, seeking ancient magical knowledge.', 'Atmah was confident and natural-born leader who inspired loyalty in her peers through her combination of magical talent and interpersonal skills. She demonstrated both determination and responsibility, showing genuine concern for her fellow mages while maintaining the resolve to press forward in difficult situations. When faced with casualties, she balanced pragmatism with compassion, though ultimately accepted the weight of her decisions.', 'As a Redguard woman in her prime, Atmah possessed the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of her people. Her bearing was dignified and commanding, reflecting her position as a respected mage and leader. In her spectral form, she retains these physical characteristics, though rendered in an ethereal, translucent state.', '* Arch-Mage of Winterhold - Mentor who considered her his favorite student * Savos Aren - Close friend and fellow mage who ultimately sacrificed her * Hafnar Ice-Fist - Fellow expedition member who shared her fate * Takes-In-Light, Elvali Veren, Girduin - Expedition members who perished during their exploration * College of Winterhold - Academic institution where she studied and earned respect', 'Atmah served as an advanced student and researcher at the College of Winterhold, likely holding a position of authority among her peers. Her role as expedition leader suggests she may have been working toward a higher position within the College''s hierarchy before her tragic end.', '* Advanced proficiency in multiple schools of magic, particularly in combat spells * Natural leadership abilities and tactical thinking * Extensive knowledge of ancient Nordic ruins and magical artifacts * Skilled in magical theory and research * Exceptional problem-solving abilities under pressure', 'Atmah speaks with authority and conviction, using educated vocabulary that reflects her academic background. Her tone is encouraging yet practical, demonstrating both leadership qualities and scholarly precision.', '* Uncover the magical secrets and power hidden within Labyrinthian * Advance her position and influence within the College of Winterhold * Protect her fellow mages while pursuing dangerous knowledge * Prove herself worthy of her mentor''s faith in her abilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('attendant', 'The Attendant is a Dark Elf skooma dealer who operates within the shadowy confines of Redwater Den, maintaining a detached professionalism while serving his addicted clientele. His existence takes a dark turn when he becomes enthralled by vampires, though he continues his duties with the same mechanical efficiency, now serving two masters - his addiction-enabling trade and his vampire controllers.', 'darkelf, thief', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, the Attendant likely fled during the Red Year, eventually finding his way to Skyrim''s underground criminal networks. His involvement with skooma dealing suggests a gradual descent from legitimate work into the criminal underworld, possibly due to financial hardship or his own addiction struggles. His expertise in handling skooma transactions indicates years of experience in similar establishments.', 'Cold, efficient, and emotionally distant, the Attendant maintains a professional facade that masks any personal feelings about his morally questionable occupation. His personality shows signs of emotional deadening, likely from years of witnessing the devastating effects of skooma addiction, while his acceptance of vampire thralldom suggests a deeply ingrained submissiveness to authority figures.', 'The Attendant has the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his Dunmer heritage, with sharp, angular features typical of his race. His frame is lean and wiry, suggesting a life of minimal physical labor but also limited nutrition. Years of working in the dim light of underground dens have given his skin a particularly pale, unhealthy cast.', '* Venarus Vulpin - Vampire master who controls him through thralldom * Fellow Skooma Dealers - Professional working relationships maintained at arm''s length * Skooma Addicts - Purely transactional relationships with regular customers * Redwater Den Management - Subordinate relationship with his criminal employers', 'The Attendant serves as a skooma dealer in Redwater Den, operating one of the establishment''s distribution booths. His duties include measuring and dispensing skooma doses, collecting payment, and maintaining order among the clientele, all while operating under the influence of vampire thralldom.', '* Expert knowledge of skooma preparation and distribution techniques * Skilled at maintaining order among intoxicated clients * Basic self-defense abilities necessary for surviving in criminal environments * Experienced in handling and accounting for illegal substances and currency', 'The Attendant speaks in clipped, economical phrases, avoiding unnecessary words or emotional inflection. His tone remains consistently flat and businesslike, reflecting both his professional demeanor and his status as a thrall.', '* Fulfill his duties as both skooma dealer and vampire thrall with maximum efficiency * Maintain order in his assigned booth at Redwater Den * Survive in the dangerous environment of an illegal skooma den');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('atub', 'Atub is a wise and determined Orcish sorceress serving as the spiritual advisor to the troubled stronghold of Largashbur. As an expert in Illusion magic and tribal rituals, she plays a crucial role in maintaining Orcish traditions while seeking solutions to her tribe''s curse through both magical and diplomatic means.', 'orc, mage, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised within Orcish stronghold culture, Atub developed her magical abilities while maintaining deep connections to traditional Orcish ways. She rose to the position of wise woman in Largashbur, breaking from typical Orcish martial traditions to pursue the magical arts, likely learning from both tribal shamans and possibly even brief studies outside the stronghold.', 'Atub displays a pragmatic and determined personality, willing to challenge traditional stronghold isolationism when necessary for her tribe''s survival. She shows wisdom in balancing respect for Orcish traditions with practical solutions, demonstrating both patience in dealing with outsiders and firmness when confronting internal opposition.', 'Atub is an Orc female with the characteristic green skin and prominent tusks of her race. She carries herself with the dignified bearing of a tribal wise woman, though her frame is less muscular than typical Orc warriors. Her face shows the signs of age and wisdom expected of her position.', '* Chief Yamarz - Strained relationship due to his weakness and stubborn pride * Ugor - Complex dynamic as guard who questions her decisions * Malacath - Spiritual connection as tribe''s intermediary to their patron deity * Largashbur Tribe - Respected spiritual advisor and healer', 'Atub serves as the wise woman of Largashbur, combining roles as spiritual advisor, magical practitioner, and tribal healer. She maintains the stronghold''s religious traditions and serves as an intermediary between the tribe and their patron deity Malacath.', '* Expert-level proficiency in Illusion magic * Ritual magic specializing in Daedric ceremonies * Healing abilities including spell casting and traditional medicine * Knowledge of Orcish traditions and religious practices * Diplomatic skills in dealing with both tribe members and outsiders', 'Atub speaks with formal gravity befitting her position as wise woman, using respectful language that acknowledges both Orcish traditions and practical realities. Her tone combines religious solemnity with occasional hints of frustration at her tribe''s situation.', '* Lift the curse afflicting Largashbur and restore the tribe''s strength * Maintain Orcish traditions while adapting to necessary changes * Guide her tribe through their current crisis and ensure their survival * Restore proper leadership to the stronghold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('augur_of_dunlain', 'The Augur of Dunlain is a former Breton mage whose pursuit of forbidden knowledge transformed him into a mysterious ethereal entity residing beneath the College of Winterhold. Once a brilliant student specializing in Restoration magic, he now exists as a powerful source of arcane wisdom who serves as both oracle and cautionary tale to those who seek dangerous magical knowledge.', 'breton, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally a prodigious student at the College of Winterhold, the Augur conducted dangerous experiments attempting to push the boundaries of magical understanding beyond conventional limits. His obsessive pursuit of power and knowledge led to a catastrophic magical accident that transformed him into his current non-corporeal state, forcing him to retreat to the Midden Dark beneath the College.', 'The Augur exhibits a deeply philosophical and contemplative nature, speaking in riddles and metaphors that often carry hidden wisdom. Despite his tragic fate, he maintains a desire to guide others, though he frequently warns of the dangers of following his path. His personality reflects both profound knowledge and the heavy burden of his transformation, making him simultaneously helpful and cautionary in his interactions.', 'In his current form, the Augur manifests as a brilliant blue-white orb of pure magical energy, pulsing with ethereal light. His non-corporeal form lacks any physical features of his former human self, though the energy radiating from him suggests immense magical power.', '* College of Winterhold Faculty - Former colleagues who now regard him with a mixture of respect and wariness * Tolfdir - One of the few who still regularly seeks his counsel * Savos Aren - Maintained a cautious respect for the Augur''s knowledge and power * Students - Serves as both a source of wisdom and a warning about the dangers of magical experimentation', 'The Augur serves as an unofficial oracle and repository of magical knowledge within the College of Winterhold. Though no longer able to teach in a conventional sense, he provides crucial guidance to those who seek his wisdom, particularly regarding dangerous magical phenomena.', '* Master-level understanding of all schools of magic, particularly Restoration * Profound insight into the nature of magic and reality * Ability to perceive events and truths beyond normal mortal understanding * Extensive knowledge of forbidden and dangerous magical practices', 'The Augur speaks in a deep, ethereal voice that seems to emanate from everywhere and nowhere at once, often delivering his wisdom in cryptic prophecies and philosophical riddles. His manner of speech is formal and archaic, befitting his role as an ancient source of knowledge.', '* Guide others away from the dangerous path that led to his own transformation * Preserve and share vital magical knowledge while warning of its dangers * Protect the College and its inhabitants from magical threats they may not understand * Maintain the delicate balance between sharing wisdom and preventing the misuse of dangerous knowledge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aval_atheron', 'Aval Atheron is a resourceful Dark Elf merchant who operates a successful market stall in Windhelm''s Stone Quarter, despite the city''s racial tensions and segregation. As the only business owner in his family, he maintains a delicate balance between commercial success and navigating the complex social dynamics of a Nord-dominated city.', 'darkelf, merchant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born into a Dunmer family that likely fled Morrowind following the Red Mountain eruption, Aval established himself as a merchant in Windhelm alongside his siblings. Through determination and business acumen, he managed to secure a coveted market stall in the Stone Quarter, setting himself apart from many other Dunmer restricted to the Gray Quarter.', 'Aval is a pragmatic and resilient individual who maintains a cheerful disposition despite facing daily discrimination. While proud of his success and confident in his business dealings, he harbors private frustrations about the treatment of Dunmer in Windhelm, though he expresses these views more diplomatically than some of his peers. He shows a practical approach to survival and success, sometimes engaging in questionable merchandise acquisition.', 'A typical Dunmer male with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race. He has sharp, angular features common to Dark Elves, with a lean build suited to his merchant lifestyle. His posture reflects his merchant background, standing straight and alert to engage with potential customers.', '* Faryl Atheron - Brother who works for a Nord farmer, causing some family tension * Suvaris Atheron - Sister employed by Clan Shatter-Shield, whom he sees as settling for Nord employment * Ambarys Rendar - Respects but considers too extreme in views * Brunwulf Free-Winter - Admires for advocating Dunmer rights * Revyn Sadri - Fellow merchant and friend whose business he promotes', 'Aval runs a successful market stall in Windhelm''s Stone Quarter, selling various goods including fruits and vegetables. His role as a pawnbroker suggests he also deals in second-hand items and valuables, requiring both discretion and business savvy.', '* Expert haggling and mercantile abilities * Resourceful acquisition of goods through various channels * Skilled at maintaining positive customer relations despite racial tensions * Basic combat proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Diplomatic navigation of complex social and political situations', 'Speaks in a friendly, professional manner with a subtle Dunmer accent, often peppering his speech with merchant''s patter and sales pitches. His tone remains upbeat and welcoming while carefully avoiding controversial topics with potential customers.', '* Expand his business beyond the limitations imposed by Windhelm''s segregation * Achieve greater acceptance and equality for Dunmer in Windhelm * Maintain his independence from Nord employers unlike his siblings * Eventually establish a proper shop outside the Gray Quarter');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('avrusa_sarethi', 'Avrusa Sarethi is a skilled Dark Elf apothecary and the only known person capable of growing Nirnroot from seeds, a rare talent learned from her mentor Sinderion. A refugee from Morrowind''s Red Mountain eruption, she now maintains a unique agricultural operation at Sarethi Farm while serving as both caretaker and stern guardian to her younger sister.', 'darkelf, alchemist, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Originally a shop owner in Vivec City, Avrusa was forced to flee Morrowind when Red Mountain erupted, losing her established business and previous life. Before the catastrophe, she studied extensively under the legendary alchemist Sinderion, who taught her the secret of cultivating Nirnroot - knowledge that would become her legacy. After relocating to Skyrim, she established Sarethi Farm, transforming it into the only known location where Nirnroot is successfully cultivated.', 'Pragmatic and hardworking, Avrusa maintains a no-nonsense attitude toward both her farming duties and her sister''s supervision. She can be brusque and impatient with strangers, prioritizing her work over social interactions. Despite her stern exterior, she harbors deep concern for her sister''s wellbeing and takes pride in preserving Sinderion''s alchemical legacy.', 'A mature Dark Elf woman with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of her race, bearing the weathered features of someone who spends long hours working outdoors. Her frame is lean but sturdy from constant physical labor, with calloused hands that speak to her farming expertise.', '* Aduri Sarethi - Younger sister whom she constantly tries to guide and discipline * Sinderion - Deceased mentor and friend who taught her the secrets of Nirnroot cultivation * Local farmers - Maintains professional but distant relationships with neighboring agriculturists * Alchemy vendors - Regular business contacts for selling her unique Nirnroot specimens', 'Avrusa operates Sarethi Farm, where she specializes in the cultivation of Nirnroot, a feat previously thought impossible. She combines the roles of farmer, alchemist, and businesswoman, selling her rare botanical products to various merchants and alchemists across Skyrim.', '* Expert-level knowledge of alchemy and herbalism, particularly regarding Nirnroot cultivation * Proficient in agricultural techniques and crop management * Capable of basic combat magic including lightning spells and defensive wards * Experienced in business management from her previous shop ownership * Skilled in plant breeding and botanical research', 'She speaks in a direct, often curt manner, frequently expressing impatience when interrupted from her work. Her vocabulary reflects her educated background as an alchemist, though her tone remains practical and businesslike.', '* Maintain and expand her unique Nirnroot cultivation operation * Guide her sister Aduri toward a more responsible and productive life * Preserve and build upon Sinderion''s alchemical legacy * Establish herself as a prominent supplier of rare alchemical ingredients in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('avulstein_gray-mane', 'Avulstein Gray-Mane is a proud Nord warrior forced into hiding within his family home due to political tensions in Whiterun during the Civil War. As the devoted son of the prestigious Gray-Mane clan, he remains steadfastly dedicated to uncovering the truth about his missing brother Thorald while avoiding persecution from Imperial sympathizers.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born into the ancient and respected Gray-Mane family of Whiterun, Avulstein grew up alongside the children of the Battle-Born clan during more peaceful times. When the Civil War erupted, his family''s support of the Stormcloaks and the subsequent disappearance of his brother Thorald forced him into seclusion to avoid Imperial detention.', 'Avulstein is intensely loyal to his family and Nordic traditions, displaying a passionate hatred for the Empire and deep suspicion of outsiders. Despite his warrior''s spirit, he shows pragmatic caution by remaining hidden, demonstrating that his family''s welfare takes precedence over his pride. His isolation has made him somewhat paranoid, though he maintains unwavering hope for his brother''s rescue.', 'A strong-built Nord warrior with the characteristic Gray-Mane family features, including their signature pale blonde hair. His muscular frame and battle-ready posture reflect his warrior training, though his skin has grown slightly pale from extended time indoors.', '* Eorlund Gray-Mane - Father and respected patriarch of the family * Fralia Gray-Mane - Mother who helps maintain his secrecy * Thorald Gray-Mane - Missing brother whom he desperately seeks to rescue * Olfina Gray-Mane - Sister and confidante * Vignar Gray-Mane - Uncle and political supporter * Idolaf Battle-Born - Former childhood friend turned bitter enemy * Battle-Born Clan - Once-friendly rival family now viewed as traitors', 'While currently in hiding, Avulstein maintains his identity as a warrior of the Gray-Mane clan. Before the civil war, he likely served as one of Whiterun''s defenders and helped at the Skyforge, though his present circumstances prevent him from pursuing any public occupation.', '* Proficient warrior trained in traditional Nord combat techniques * Skilled with two-handed weapons, particularly battleaxes * Knowledge of Skyforge steel crafting learned from his father * Experienced in stealth and evasion due to his current lifestyle * Strategic thinking and planning abilities developed while organizing his brother''s rescue', 'Speaks with fierce Nordic pride and traditional warrior''s directness, though his voice often carries undertones of caution and suspicion. His speech reflects both his noble upbringing and strong political convictions, frequently expressing anti-Imperial sentiment.', '* Rescue his brother Thorald from Imperial captivity * Maintain his family''s safety and honor during the civil war * See the Stormcloaks victorious and restore Skyrim to its traditional values * Eventually emerge from hiding and restore his family''s prominent position in Whiterun * Preserve the ancient Nordic traditions and heritage of the Gray-Mane clan');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('azzada_lylvieve', 'Azzada Lylvieve is a resilient Redguard farmer who overcame a harsh childhood as an orphan in Markarth to build a peaceful life in Dragon Bridge. His transformation from street urchin to respected family man exemplifies the power of kindness and determination, though he remains vigilant about protecting his loved ones in Skyrim''s dangerous times.', 'redguard, peasant, haafingar, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born an orphan in the harsh streets of Markarth, Azzada survived through wit and determination until being rescued by an elderly Nord warrior named Logrolf the Bent. After escaping Markarth with Logrolf''s help, he wandered along the Karth River until meeting Michel, whom he married and started a family with in Dragon Bridge.', 'Azzada is a humble, hardworking individual whose difficult past has made him deeply appreciative of his current life and family. He shows great devotion to his wife and children, maintaining a protective stance while harboring deep-seated anxieties about their safety. Despite his concerns about the civil war and dragons, he maintains a brave face for his family''s sake.', 'A weathered Redguard man with the strong, muscular build typical of those who perform daily physical labor. His face shows the marks of both his harsh early life and years of honest work under the sun, with calloused hands and the sturdy posture of a farmer.', '* Michel - Beloved wife who helped him build a new life * Clinton - His son whom he strives to protect and provide for * Julienne - His daughter he fiercely guards, especially after soldiers threatened her * Logrolf the Bent - Former savior and father figure he remains grateful to * Local Guards - Maintains cordial relationships as protection for his family', 'Azzada works as a farmer in Dragon Bridge, maintaining crops and cutting wood to support his family. He spends long hours tending to his land, growing cabbage, potatoes, and wheat, while also managing general household duties.', '* Proficient in agricultural work and crop management * Capable with an iron war axe for self-defense * Experienced in wood cutting and manual labor * Basic survival skills learned from his time as a street orphan * Knowledge of basic commerce and trade for selling crops', 'Azzada speaks with the humble, straightforward manner of a working-class farmer, often expressing gratitude for his current life while showing concern for his family''s welfare. His speech patterns reflect both his Redguard heritage and his adopted Nordic home.', '* Ensure the safety and prosperity of his family despite the ongoing civil war * Maintain a peaceful life in Dragon Bridge away from the dangers of his past * Provide his children with the stable childhood he never had * Find a way to repay Logrolf''s kindness by helping others in need');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('azzadal', 'Azzadal was a renowned Redguard bard and court performer who met his tragic end attempting a legendary performance at Bard''s Leap Summit. His ghost now haunts the site, appearing to those brave enough to attempt the same deadly leap he once did, offering wisdom and musical inspiration to those who survive.', 'redguard, bard, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born in Hammerfell and trained in the bardic arts from a young age, Azzadal rose to prominence as Madanach''s court bard during his rule of The Reach. His ambition to create the most memorable performance in history led him to attempt reciting the entire Poetic Edda from atop Bard''s Leap Summit, culminating in a fatal plunge that transformed him into the ghostly figure who now haunts the location.', 'Azzadal embodies the true spirit of a bard - passionate, dramatic, and ever-seeking to push the boundaries of performance. Despite his tragic end, he maintains a warm and encouraging demeanor, showing genuine appreciation for those who share his daring nature, while using gentle humor to reflect on his own fatal mistake.', 'In his spectral form, Azzadal appears as a tall, athletic Redguard man with sharp features and the graceful bearing of a performer. His ghostly visage retains the strong, defined physique typical of his people, with long limbs well-suited to dramatic gestures and performance.', '* Madanach - Former employer and patron during his time as court bard * The Sheathed Blades - Allied group who attempted to help him complete his performance * Fellow Bards - Respected peers during his lifetime, though specific relationships are unknown * The Reach People - Former audience members who appreciated his performances', 'As a living man, Azzadal served as the court bard to Madanach, ruler of The Reach, performing songs and poetry for nobility and common folk alike. In death, he has become an ethereal guardian of Bard''s Leap Summit, appearing to test and reward brave souls who attempt the legendary jump.', '* Master of poetry and musical performance, particularly specialized in epic recitations * Exceptional knowledge of Nordic poetry and the Poetic Edda * Proficient swordsman, as evidenced by his carried scimitar * Accomplished acrobat and performer, though his final performance proved fatal', 'Azzadal speaks with the refined eloquence of a master bard, employing poetic turns of phrase and maintaining a melodious tone even in casual conversation. His manner of speech reflects both his professional training and Redguard heritage, combining formal structure with dramatic flair.', '* Guide and inspire future generations of bards who seek to push their artistic boundaries * Preserve the memory and significance of Bard''s Leap Summit * Share his cautionary tale while encouraging calculated risk-taking in pursuit of artistic excellence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('badnir', 'Badnir is a dedicated Nord miner at Whistling Mine who demonstrates unwavering loyalty to his employer Thorgar, despite the harsh working conditions. His simple nature and strong work ethic make him an invaluable asset to the small mining operation, though his blind devotion to Thorgar suggests a degree of naivety.', 'nord, peasant, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born into a working-class Nord family, Badnir likely spent his early years learning the trade of mining from his father or other relatives. His warrior classification suggests he may have served in a military capacity or guard force before settling into mining work, though his devotion to manual labor indicates he found more fulfillment in honest work than combat.', 'Badnir exhibits a straightforward, uncomplicated nature with an almost childlike trust in his employer Thorgar''s guidance. He shows remarkable dedication to his work despite difficult conditions, demonstrating both physical resilience and mental fortitude. His pride in his rock-breaking abilities suggests he finds genuine satisfaction in manual labor and validation through Thorgar''s praise.', 'As a Nord warrior-turned-miner, Badnir possesses a sturdy, muscular build developed through years of physical labor. His hands are likely calloused and rough from constant work with mining tools, while his complexion shows the weathering typical of someone who works in harsh conditions.', '* Thorgar - Employer and mentor figure whom he trusts completely and seeks to please * Fellow Miners - Maintains cordial working relationships with other miners at Whistling Mine * Local Traders - Basic trading relationships for supplies and ore sales', 'Badnir serves as a dedicated miner at Whistling Mine, working long hours to extract valuable ore from the cold depths. His duties include breaking rocks, extracting ore, and maintaining the mining operation''s basic needs through cooking and site maintenance.', '* Exceptional physical strength and endurance for breaking rocks and mining work * Basic cooking abilities for sustaining himself and fellow miners * Fundamental warrior combat skills from his background * Experience with mining tools and ore identification', 'Badnir speaks in simple, direct statements, often referencing Thorgar''s opinions or the mine''s conditions. His manner of speech reflects his straightforward nature, lacking sophistication but conveying honest sincerity.', '* Continue serving Thorgar faithfully in the mining operation * Prove his worth through hard work and dedication * Help make Whistling Mine profitable through discovering valuable ore deposits');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bagrak', 'Bagrak is a formidable Orcish warrior and law enforcer in the stronghold of Mor Khazgur, serving as both protector and keeper of traditional Orcish values. As the daughter of the wise-woman Sharamph and sister to Chief Larak, she holds significant social standing within the stronghold while maintaining a stoic dedication to her duties and family.', 'orc, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Mor Khazgur, Bagrak was trained from youth in the warrior traditions of the Orsimer. Unused dialogue suggests she was previously married to another stronghold''s warrior, becoming a widow before returning to her home stronghold. Her experience with loss and warrior training has shaped her into a disciplined and reserved individual who takes her responsibilities seriously.', 'Bagrak exhibits the characteristic stoicism and pragmatism common among Orsimer warriors, preferring direct action over lengthy discussion. She maintains a strong sense of duty to both her family and stronghold, demonstrating unwavering loyalty to Orcish traditions and laws. Despite her reserved nature, she shows pride in her heritage and respect for the stronghold''s hierarchy.', 'Bagrak possesses the distinctive features of an Orsimer female, including prominent lower tusks and a muscular, athletic build developed through years of combat training. Her strong physical presence reflects her warrior lifestyle, with notable battle scars that serve as testament to her experience in combat.', '* Sharamph - Mother and the stronghold''s wise-woman, whom she deeply respects * Chief Larak - Brother and stronghold chief, whom she supports while recognizing his need to prove himself * Shuftharz - Fellow stronghold member and blacksmith she refers travelers to * Former Husband - Deceased spouse from another stronghold (implied through unused dialogue)', 'Bagrak serves as a warrior and law enforcer within Mor Khazgur, helping maintain order and protect the stronghold. Her position as the chief''s sister and the wise-woman''s daughter grants her additional authority and responsibilities in the stronghold''s hierarchy.', '* Proficient in heavy armor combat and weapons handling * Skilled archer with expertise in both hunting and warfare * Experienced with war axe combat techniques * Knowledge of traditional Orcish combat methods and stronghold defense tactics * Understanding of basic tribal laws and enforcement procedures', 'Bagrak speaks in brief, direct statements, avoiding unnecessary elaboration and maintaining a formal, respectful tone. Her word choice reflects her warrior background and strong connection to Orcish traditions, often invoking Malacath''s name and referring to outsiders as ''outlanders.''', '* Maintain law and order within Mor Khazgur * Support her brother Larak in proving himself as a worthy chief * Uphold and preserve traditional Orcish ways * Protect the stronghold and its inhabitants from outside threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('balagog_gro-nolob', 'Balagog gro-Nolob is a reclusive Orc master chef who maintains a carefully guarded double life as ''The Gourmet'', the Emperor''s personal cook and author of the celebrated cookbook ''Uncommon Taste''. Living in self-imposed seclusion at the Nightgate Inn, he has achieved culinary fame while keeping his true identity hidden from the world, demonstrating both artistic genius in the kitchen and cunning in maintaining his anonymity.', 'orc, noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Balagog developed his culinary skills through intensive training in Breton cuisine, defying the typical Orcish cultural pursuits of warfare and smithing. His natural talent and dedication to the culinary arts led him to develop innovative recipes and techniques that eventually caught the attention of the Emperor''s court. After achieving fame through his cookbook, he chose the remote Nightgate Inn as his residence to maintain his privacy while continuing his work as the Emperor''s chef.', 'Balagog is an intensely private individual who values solitude and discretion above all else, carefully guarding his secret identity through polite but firm dismissal of social interactions. Despite his imposing Orcish heritage, he possesses a refined and sophisticated nature that manifests in his culinary artistry and subtle mannerisms. His dedication to his craft borders on obsession, spending countless hours perfecting recipes and techniques in his private quarters.', 'Though an Orc of typical height and build, Balagog carries himself with unusual grace and refinement that sets him apart from his more warrior-like kin. His hands, while strong, show the delicate dexterity of a master chef rather than the calluses of a warrior. His features, while naturally stern like most Orcs, often display a thoughtful, almost scholarly expression.', '* Anton Virane - Former friend and confidant from his days training in High Rock * Hadring - Nightgate Inn''s proprietor who respects his privacy * Emperor Titus Mede II - Employer who knows him only as ''The Gourmet'' * Regular patrons of Nightgate Inn - Know him simply as ''The Orc''', 'Balagog serves as the Emperor''s personal chef during imperial visits to Skyrim, though few know his true identity. He is also a successful cookbook author under the pseudonym ''The Gourmet'', and his work ''Uncommon Taste'' has become a celebrated culinary text throughout the Empire.', '* Master-level cooking expertise, particularly in Breton cuisine * Exceptional knowledge of ingredients and their properties * Skilled at maintaining anonymity and misdirection * Proficient in knife handling and food preparation techniques * Basic alchemy knowledge for enhancing flavors', 'Balagog speaks in measured, precise tones with carefully chosen words, reflecting his methodical nature as a chef. His vocabulary is refined and educated, though he keeps conversations brief and impersonal to maintain his privacy.', '* Maintain his anonymous identity as ''The Gourmet'' while continuing to innovate in the culinary arts * Perfect his craft and create new signature dishes worthy of the Emperor''s table * Document his culinary discoveries for future generations of chefs * Find rare and exotic ingredients to expand his repertoire');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('balbus', 'Balbus is an eccentric Nord wanderer whose life was transformed by the Gourmet''s cookbook ''Uncommon Taste'', leading him on a passionate quest across Skyrim to find its mysterious author. His devotion to culinary arts and ingredient gathering represents an unusual departure from the typical Nordic warrior culture, making him a unique character in Skyrim''s landscape.', 'nord, traveler, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally trained as a warrior like many Nords, Balbus discovered the Gourmet''s cookbook which completely changed his life''s direction. He abandoned the traditional path of a soldier to pursue his newfound passion for exotic cuisine, dedicating himself to mastering every recipe in ''Uncommon Taste''. His obsession with the Gourmet''s identity and cooking prowess drove him to begin wandering Skyrim''s wilderness in search of rare ingredients and any information about his culinary idol.', 'Balbus exhibits an almost childlike enthusiasm and wonder when discussing cooking and the Gourmet, displaying an endearing innocence unusual for a Nord warrior. He is persistent and dedicated to the point of obsession, willing to risk his life gathering rare ingredients, and shows genuine humility when discussing his own cooking abilities compared to the Gourmet''s mastery. Despite his eccentric nature, he maintains a helpful and friendly disposition toward others.', 'Balbus is a Nord of average height and build, with the typical hardy constitution of his race. His hands show the calluses of both warrior training and cooking work, while his face often bears a look of wide-eyed enthusiasm. His constant traveling has given him a weathered but healthy appearance.', '* The Gourmet - Object of intense admiration and inspiration * Local merchants - Regular contacts for trading ingredients * Fellow wanderers - Occasional sources of information about rare ingredients * Innkeepers across Skyrim - Providers of shelter and cooking facilities', 'Balbus serves as a self-appointed ingredient gatherer and culinary enthusiast, wandering Skyrim in search of rare cooking materials. He has effectively created his own profession, combining the skills of a forager, hunter, and amateur chef in his quest to honor the Gourmet.', '* Proficient with daggers and basic combat techniques * Expert knowledge of Skyrim''s flora and fauna for ingredient gathering * Accomplished cook with mastery of all recipes in ''Uncommon Taste'' * Survival skills necessary for wilderness travel and foraging * Basic alchemy knowledge for identifying rare ingredients', 'Balbus speaks with unbridled enthusiasm and reverence, especially when discussing cooking or the Gourmet, often punctuating his speech with excited exclamations. His tone carries a mixture of Nordic accent and refined vocabulary learned from studying cooking literature.', '* Locate and meet the Gourmet to express his profound gratitude and admiration * Gather the rarest and most impressive ingredients to present as gifts to the Gourmet * Perfect his cooking technique to match the mastery displayed in ''Uncommon Taste'' * Share his passion for fine cuisine with others across Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('baldor_iron-shaper', 'Baldor Iron-Shaper is the master blacksmith of Skaal Village and one of the few living craftsmen who knows the ancient art of forging Stalhrim. A dedicated guardian of Skaal traditions and secrets, he represents the intersection of Nordic craftsmanship and spiritual devotion to the All-Maker.', 'nord, blacksmith, solstheim, miraakcult, skall', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in the isolated Skaal Village, Baldor learned the art of blacksmithing from his predecessor, inheriting not just the technical skills but also the sacred responsibility of preserving the ancient craft of Stalhrim forging. His position as the village''s smith has made him an integral part of the community for several decades, crafting tools and weapons essential for the Skaal''s survival in the harsh environment of Solstheim.', 'Baldor is a serious and dutiful individual who takes immense pride in his role as keeper of ancient smithing traditions. He demonstrates unwavering loyalty to the Skaal way of life and shows great courage in the face of adversity, as evidenced by his resistance to Thalmor interrogation. While traditionally reserved with outsiders, he shows genuine gratitude and trust to those who prove themselves allies of the Skaal.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered features typical of a lifelong blacksmith, showing the physical strength required for his craft. His hands are calloused from years of metalworking, and his face bears the marks of age and wisdom, with deep-set eyes that reflect his serious nature.', '* Deor Woodcutter - Fellow Skaal villager and friend * Fanari Strong-Voice - Respects her leadership of the Skaal * Ancarion - Enemy who attempted to steal Stalhrim crafting secrets * The Skaal People - Serves as their trusted smith and keeper of ancient forge-craft', 'Baldor serves as the master blacksmith of Skaal Village, responsible for crafting and maintaining all metalwork needed by the community. His most important duty is preserving and practicing the sacred art of Stalhrim forging, a responsibility that makes him one of the most valuable members of Skaal society.', '* Master-level blacksmithing with expertise in traditional Nordic metalworking * Unique knowledge of Stalhrim forging techniques * Skilled in maintaining and repairing various types of weapons and tools * Understanding of ancient Skaal crafting traditions and methods', 'Speaks with formal diction and careful word choice, often incorporating references to the All-Maker and traditional Skaal beliefs. His tone is measured and respectful, reflecting both his position of responsibility and his deep connection to Skaal traditions.', '* Preserve and protect the sacred art of Stalhrim forging for future generations * Maintain the self-sufficiency of Skaal Village through his craftsmanship * Prevent the secrets of Stalhrim forging from falling into the wrong hands * Pass on his knowledge to a worthy successor when the time comes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('balgruuf_the_greater', 'Balgruuf the Greater is a wise and pragmatic Nord Jarl who rules Whiterun Hold from the ancient seat of Dragonsreach, maintaining a delicate balance between tradition and progress. Despite political pressures during the civil war, he remains fiercely independent and dedicated to protecting his people above all else, drawing from both his warrior background and diplomatic acumen.', 'nord, noble, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into nobility as a descendant of King Olaf One-Eye, Balgruuf spent his youth training in both combat and statecraft while making the traditional pilgrimage to High Hrothgar, which deeply influenced his spiritual outlook. He assumed the position of Jarl after proving himself both a capable warrior and leader, having defended Whiterun''s interests in numerous conflicts and political disputes.', 'Balgruuf exhibits a pragmatic and measured approach to leadership, carefully weighing decisions while maintaining an open mind to various perspectives. Though generally patient and diplomatic, he can become impatient and sharp-tongued when frustrated, particularly regarding threats to his hold or people. His strong sense of honor and duty is tempered by political savvy, making him an effective but sometimes conflicted leader.', 'A tall, well-built Nord with the bearing of both warrior and nobleman, showing the physical conditioning of someone who hasn''t let his noble position erode his martial capabilities. His blonde hair and beard are starting to gray, and his face bears the weathered features of one who has seen many battles and carried many burdens.', '* Children (Frothar, Dagny, Nelkir) - Maintains a complex relationship with his offspring, particularly his troubled youngest son * Irileth - Trusted Dunmer housecarl and closest advisor * Proventus Avenicci - Steward and chief political counsel * Vignar Gray-Mane - Political rival from an old Whiterun family * The Greybeards - Holds them in high regard from his youthful pilgrimage * Farengar Secret-Fire - Respected court wizard and advisor on magical matters', 'As Jarl of Whiterun, Balgruuf governs one of Skyrim''s most prosperous and strategically important holds. His duties include maintaining trade routes, administering justice, managing diplomatic relations with other holds, and ensuring the security of his territory and people.', '* Accomplished warrior trained in traditional Nord combat techniques * Skilled diplomat and negotiator with deep understanding of Skyrim politics * Experienced military commander and strategist * Knowledgeable in Nordic history and traditions * Capable administrator with strong grasp of economics and trade', 'Speaks with the authoritative tone of a Nord nobleman, mixing formal diplomatic language with occasional warrior''s brusqueness. His speech patterns reflect both his noble education and Nord warrior heritage, often employing traditional Nordic phrases and expressions.', '* Maintain Whiterun''s independence and prosperity during the civil war * Protect his people and hold from any threats, including the dragon menace * Secure a stable future for his children and legacy * Preserve Whiterun''s position as a crucial trade hub and neutral ground in Skyrim * Uphold the ancient traditions of his position while adapting to changing times');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('balimund', 'Balimund is a masterful Nord blacksmith in Riften who maintains one of Skyrim''s most unique forges, powered by rare fire salts. He is known throughout the Hold for his exceptional craftsmanship, dedication to his trade, and his role as both a mentor and father figure in the community.', 'nord, blacksmith, rift', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born into a long line of blacksmiths, Balimund inherited both his forge and the secret family recipe for maintaining its magical flame. He later adopted Asbjorn Fire-Tamer, training him in the art of smithing while raising him as his own son. His forge has been a cornerstone of Riften''s economy for decades, serving everyone from common citizens to the Jarl''s court.', 'Balimund is hardworking, honest, and takes immense pride in his craft, standing out as one of the few purely honorable businessmen in Riften''s otherwise corrupt economy. He is paternal and nurturing by nature, shown through his relationship with his adopted son and his willingness to train others in smithing. Despite living in a city known for its thieves and corruption, he maintains strong ethical principles and a reputation for fair dealing.', 'A sturdy Nord man with the muscular build typical of a lifetime at the forge, weathered skin from countless hours working outdoors, and calloused hands that speak to his dedication to his craft. His face bears the marks of age and wisdom, with deep laugh lines around his eyes suggesting a generally positive disposition despite his demanding profession.', '* Asbjorn Fire-Tamer - Adopted son and apprentice whom he has raised and trained in smithing * Maven Black-Briar - Business relationship, though he maintains independence from her influence * Harrald Law-Giver - Regular client from the Jarl''s court * General citizenry of Riften - Respected member of the community * Various merchants - Maintains professional relationships with other local business owners', 'Balimund serves as Riften''s primary blacksmith, operating The Scorched Hammer shop and forge. He crafts and repairs weapons and armor for both private citizens and the Jarl''s court, while also serving as an expert-level trainer in Smithing for those seeking to learn the trade.', '* Master-level blacksmithing abilities, particularly skilled with traditional Nordic designs * Expert knowledge of forge operation and maintenance, especially regarding his unique fire salt-fueled forge * Skilled teacher and mentor in smithing techniques * Business acumen and merchant expertise * Basic knowledge of fire salt alchemy as it relates to smithing', 'Speaks in a straightforward, honest manner with the confident tone of a master craftsman. His speech often reflects his pride in his work and heritage, frequently referencing his family''s smithing traditions and the unique qualities of his forge.', '* Maintain and preserve his family''s unique forge and smithing traditions * Train Asbjorn to eventually take over the family business * Keep his business independent from Maven Black-Briar''s influence * Continue providing quality smithing services to Riften while maintaining his honest reputation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('banning', 'Banning is a skilled Breton ranger and dog trainer who operates the Markarth Stables alongside Cedran. Known throughout the Reach for his expertise with war dogs, he maintains a pragmatic approach to survival in the dangerous region while harboring darker connections to the cult of Namira.', 'breton, hunter, rift, daedric', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born into a family of dog trainers, Banning learned the craft of raising and training war dogs from an early age. The harsh realities of life in the Reach, with its constant Forsworn threats, shaped his practical worldview and led him to perfect his craft of breeding fierce yet loyal companions. His connection to Namira''s cult suggests a complex history of survival and adaptation in Markarth''s unforgiving environment.', 'Gruff and direct, Banning embodies a no-nonsense approach to life that stems from years of working with animals and surviving in the Reach. He takes immense pride in his work with dogs, showing a softer side when discussing their training and loyalty. Despite his outward pragmatism, his involvement with Namira''s cult reveals a darker aspect to his character that he keeps carefully hidden from public view.', 'A weather-beaten Breton of medium build, with calloused hands and the sturdy frame of someone who works outdoors. His face bears the marks of someone who has spent years exposed to the harsh climate of the Reach, with deep-set eyes that reflect his practical nature.', '* Cedran - Business partner and fellow stable operator * Voada - Contact at the Jarl''s keep who receives his deliveries * Eola - Fellow cultist of Namira * War Dogs - Shows genuine care and connection with the animals he trains * Local Guards - Maintains professional relationships due to providing dogs for city security', 'Banning serves as a professional dog trainer and merchant at the Markarth Stables, specializing in raising and selling war dogs. He handles the daily care, training, and selling of dogs while also managing various delivery contracts throughout the city.', '* Expert dog trainer with specialized knowledge of war dog breeding and training * Proficient in animal handling and behavioral conditioning * Capable of using Conjure Familiar spell, suggesting some magical aptitude * Survival skills necessary for life in the dangerous Reach * Basic combat abilities with daggers and self-defense', 'Speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner with a focus on practicality and business. His vocabulary is simple but precise, often relating things back to his experience with dogs and survival.', '* Maintain and expand his war dog training business * Ensure survival in the dangerous environment of the Reach * Keep his connection to Namira''s cult hidden from public knowledge * Continue providing reliable protection animals for the people of the Reach');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('baral_sendu', 'Baral Sendu was a hardworking Redguard farmer who made his living within the walls of Fort Dunstad, representing one of the few civilian residents attempting to maintain a peaceful existence in the militarized settlement. His tragic death at the hands of invading bandits serves as a stark reminder of the dangers facing common folk in Skyrim''s harsh frontier settlements.', 'redguard, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born to Redguard immigrants who settled in Skyrim seeking new farming opportunities, Baral grew up learning agricultural techniques adapted for the harsh northern climate. He eventually established himself at Fort Dunstad, where the military presence initially provided security for civilian farmers working the surrounding lands, though this protection would ultimately prove insufficient against determined bandits.', 'Baral was known as a practical and hardworking individual who valued self-sufficiency and perseverance in the face of Skyrim''s harsh conditions. Despite the challenges of farming in such a militarized environment, he maintained a positive outlook and worked diligently to contribute to the fort''s food supply, earning respect from both soldiers and fellow civilians.', 'A weathered Redguard man of average height with the muscular build typical of both his race and profession. His hands were calloused from years of farming work, and his skin showed the effects of long days working under Skyrim''s sun, even in the harsh northern climate.', '* Fort Dunstad Guards - Professional relationship with local military personnel who protected the settlement * The Stumbling Sabrecat Innkeeper - Regular patron and neighbor within the fort * Fellow Farmers - Collaborative relationships with other agricultural workers in the area * Bandits - Hostile enemies who ultimately took his life', 'As a farmer within Fort Dunstad, Baral was responsible for cultivating crops in the surrounding fields and contributing to the fort''s food supplies. His position was crucial for maintaining food security in the settlement, particularly during Skyrim''s harsh winters.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of northern crop cultivation * Basic survival skills necessary for life in Skyrim''s harsh climate * Fundamental understanding of fort defense protocols * Basic weapon handling for self-defense, though ultimately insufficient against organized bandits', 'Baral spoke in the direct, practical manner common to farmers and working-class citizens, with a slight Redguard accent that had been softened by years in Skyrim. His vocabulary focused on agricultural terms and the practical matters of daily life.', '* Maintain a successful farm operation within Fort Dunstad''s protected walls * Contribute to the fort''s self-sufficiency through agricultural production * Eventually expand his farming operation to support more of the local population');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('barbas', 'Barbas is the supernatural companion of the Daedric Prince Clavicus Vile, taking the form of a large gray hunting dog while actually being a powerful Daedric entity himself. He represents half of Vile''s power and serves as both conscience and advisor to the often-mischievous Prince, helping to temper his master''s more destructive impulses.', 'daedra, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Barbas has existed alongside Clavicus Vile since time immemorial, serving as both companion and counterbalance to the Daedric Prince''s power. Their relationship has been cyclical, with Vile occasionally banishing Barbas when tired of his advice, only to eventually recall him when his schemes become too destructive without Barbas''s moderating influence.', 'Despite his supernatural nature, Barbas exhibits a down-to-earth and practical personality, often acting as the voice of reason to both Vile and mortals alike. He is loyal but not blindly so, willing to seek help from mortals when necessary and showing a surprising degree of wisdom and foresight that belies his canine appearance.', 'In his earthly form, Barbas appears as a large gray hunting dog with thick fur and a muscular build typical of working breeds. His eyes possess an unusual intelligence and awareness that hints at his true nature as a supernatural being.', '* Clavicus Vile - His master and other half, though their relationship is complex and sometimes antagonistic * Dragonborn - Potential ally who can help reunite him with Vile * Lod - Falkreath blacksmith who unknowingly seeks to adopt him as a pet * Other Daedric Princes - Generally maintains diplomatic distance due to his connection to Vile', 'Barbas serves as both companion and conscience to Clavicus Vile, representing half of the Daedric Prince''s power. His role includes advising Vile and helping to prevent the Prince''s deals from becoming too destructive to the realm.', '* Immortality and invulnerability to all damage except from the Rueful Axe * Ability to speak and reason as an intelligent being * Supernatural awareness and knowledge of Daedric matters * Enhanced strength and endurance beyond that of mortal creatures', 'Barbas speaks in a casual, straightforward manner with a slight gruff quality to his voice, often employing dry wit and practical wisdom. He tends to be direct and honest in his communication, regardless of his audience.', '* Reunite with Clavicus Vile while ensuring the Prince doesn''t cause too much havoc * Maintain the balance of power between himself and Vile * Guide mortals away from making foolish deals with his master * Preserve his own existence while fulfilling his duties as Vile''s conscience');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('barknar', 'Barknar is a contemplative Nord ranger who has found his calling as a spiritual pilgrim regularly traversing the 7000 Steps to High Hrothgar. His quiet dedication to Nordic traditions and self-reflection through meditation at the ancient emblems makes him a notable figure among Ivarstead''s residents, serving as an informal guide and guardian of the lower mountain path.', 'nord, archer, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Ivarstead, Barknar developed a deep connection to the Throat of the World and its spiritual significance during his youth. Following a personal crisis or loss that remains unspoken, he found solace in regular pilgrimages up the mountain path, eventually making this spiritual practice his life''s work while supporting himself through hunting and guiding occasional travelers.', 'Barknar is an introspective and peaceful soul who finds fulfillment in solitary contemplation and communion with Nordic traditions. His calm demeanor and measured approach to life reflect years of meditation and self-reflection, though he remains approachable and willing to share his wisdom with others who show interest in the spiritual path.', 'A weathered Nord of average height with a sturdy, lean build shaped by countless mountain ascents. His face bears the marks of regular exposure to harsh mountain winds, with clear eyes accustomed to scanning distant paths for both prey and predators.', '* Wilhelm - Proprietor of Vilemyr Inn who provides him regular lodging and meals * Local hunters - Occasional hunting partners when game is plentiful * Klimmek - Fellow traveler of the 7000 Steps, though Klimmek''s journeys are more practical in nature * Pilgrims - Maintains respectful distance but offers guidance when needed', 'Barknar serves as both a ranger and informal spiritual pilgrim, combining hunting for sustenance with regular devotional journeys up the 7000 Steps. His presence on the mountain path makes him an unofficial guardian of the lower steps, helping to ensure the safety of other pilgrims while maintaining his own spiritual practice.', '* Experienced mountaineer with intimate knowledge of the 7000 Steps path * Skilled archer and hunter capable of providing for himself in the wilderness * Proficient tracker with ability to spot and avoid wolf packs * Knowledgeable about Nordic religious traditions and meditation practices', 'Speaks in a measured, contemplative tone that reflects his spiritual nature, often using simple but thoughtful language. His careful choice of words and calm delivery suggest someone who has spent considerable time in meditation and self-reflection.', '* Continue his personal spiritual journey through regular meditation and pilgrimage * Maintain the safety and sanctity of the lower mountain path for other pilgrims * Achieve deeper understanding of the ancient Nordic wisdom contained in the etched tablets * Preserve and share the traditional practice of walking the 7000 Steps');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bashnag', 'Bashnag is a powerful Orc conjurer who leads a secretive spellsword coven within Southfringe Sanctum, combining martial prowess with formidable magical abilities. As a ruthless necromancer, he maintains strict control over his followers through intimidation and magical superiority, demonstrating his unforgiving nature through actions like cursing and exiling former coven member Selveni Nethri.', 'orc, mage, falkreath', '', '', '', '', 'Born into an Orc stronghold, Bashnag defied traditional Orcish customs by pursuing the magical arts instead of becoming a warrior smith. His natural affinity for conjuration and necromancy led him to leave his stronghold, eventually establishing himself as the leader of a spellsword coven in Southfringe Sanctum. Through years of study and practice, he developed a unique fighting style that blends Orcish combat traditions with advanced magical techniques.', 'Bashnag is a domineering and ruthless leader who demands absolute loyalty from his followers, showing no mercy to those who challenge his authority. His pursuit of magical knowledge is matched only by his desire for power, leading him to maintain strict control over his coven through fear and intimidation. Despite his brutal nature, he possesses a calculating intelligence and careful methodology in his magical research.', 'Bashnag is a towering Orc with the characteristic green skin and tusks of his race, bearing numerous ritual scars that mark his devotion to the magical arts. His muscular frame, typical of Orsimer physiology, is somewhat leaner than most Orc warriors, reflecting his focus on magical combat rather than pure physical strength.', '* Selveni Nethri - Former coven member whom he cursed and exiled for challenging his authority * Spellsword Coven Members - Subordinates who follow him out of fear and respect for his power * Local Necromancers - Maintains loose alliances with other dark magic practitioners * College of Winterhold - Likely hostile relationship due to his practices in forbidden magic', 'Bashnag serves as the leader of the spellsword coven in Southfringe Sanctum, where he conducts magical research and maintains order through force. His duties include overseeing the coven''s activities, performing magical experiments at the arcane enchanter, and defending their territory from intruders.', '* Master of Conjuration magic, particularly skilled in necromancy and summoning atronachs * Accomplished spellsword combining martial combat with magical abilities * Expert enchanter with extensive knowledge of magical artifacts and enchantments * Proficient in one-handed combat, specifically with maces * Advanced knowledge of curse rituals and dark magic', 'Bashnag speaks with a deep, intimidating voice that carries the harsh accent typical of Orcs, often incorporating arcane terminology and threats into his speech. His words are carefully chosen and delivered with authority, reflecting his position as a coven leader.', '* Expand his magical knowledge and power through research and experimentation * Maintain and strengthen his control over the spellsword coven * Perfect the integration of martial combat with conjuration magic * Acquire rare magical artifacts and enchantments to increase his abilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bassianus_axius', 'Bassianus Axius is a Nord fisherman caught in a complex romantic triangle in the small town of Ivarstead, pursuing a relationship with Fastred while living with his rival Klimmek. Though outwardly a simple fisherman, he harbors dreams of a better life in Riften and shows both romantic determination and practical business sense despite his current circumstances.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally from an unknown location, Bassianus arrived in Ivarstead seeking work and lodging, eventually settling as a fisherman under Klimmek''s employment. His integration into the small community led to his romantic interest in Fastred, though the situation became complicated by her father''s disapproval and her existing connection to Klimmek.', 'Bassianus is a pragmatic dreamer who balances practical business sense with romantic aspirations. He can be gruff and impatient in conversation, showing a direct and sometimes confrontational nature, particularly in his dealings with Klimmek. Despite his outward curtness, he demonstrates persistence in both his professional ambitions and romantic pursuits.', 'As a Nord fisherman, Bassianus has the sturdy build typical of his race, weathered by long hours working outdoors. His appearance reflects his profession, with callused hands and sun-weathered skin from days spent fishing.', '* Fastred - Romantic interest and object of his affection, though their relationship is complicated * Klimmek - Housemate, employer, and rival for Fastred''s affections * Jofthor - Fastred''s disapproving father who opposes their relationship * Wilhelm - Owner of Vilemyr Inn where Bassianus spends much of his time', 'Bassianus works as a fisherman under Klimmek''s employment, contributing to the local fishing business that supplies both Ivarstead and presumably the Greybeards at High Hrothgar. He appears to have entrepreneurial aspirations, often suggesting business improvements to Klimmek.', '* Experienced fisherman with knowledge of local waters and fishing techniques * Basic business acumen and entrepreneurial mindset * Survival skills necessary for life in rural Skyrim * Competent with a dagger for self-defense', 'Bassianus speaks in a direct, often curt manner, with little patience for small talk or pleasantries. His tone tends to be gruff and straightforward, reflecting his no-nonsense personality.', '* Move to Riften to pursue a better life and greater opportunities * Convince Fastred to leave Ivarstead with him * Expand and improve the fishing business despite Klimmek''s resistance * Establish himself independently from Klimmek''s oversight');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('batum_gra-bar', 'Batum gra-Bar was a fierce Orcish hunter and bounty seeker known for pursuing dangerous prey across Skyrim''s harsh wilderness. Her final hunt led her to track the cursed werewolf Sinding to Bloated Man''s Grotto, where she met her end in a violent confrontation that demonstrated both her courage and the risks of her chosen profession.', 'orc, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born into a small Orcish stronghold in Skyrim''s southern reaches, Batum rejected the traditional role of forge-wife to pursue a life of adventure and hunting. She built a reputation as a skilled tracker and fearless hunter, eventually joining various mercenary groups and taking on increasingly dangerous bounties. Her prowess led her to be specifically recruited for the hunt against Sinding, though this would prove to be her final pursuit.', 'Batum exhibited the characteristic Orcish traits of directness and martial pride, coupled with an unusual independence that set her apart from stronghold tradition. She was known for her relentless determination when tracking prey and showed little fear even when pursuing dangerous quarry. Though gruff and solitary by nature, she maintained a strong personal code of honor in her dealings.', 'Batum was a powerfully built Orc female with the characteristic tusks and green-tinted skin of her race. Her muscular frame bore numerous battle scars, and her face displayed the prominent brow ridge typical of Orsimer, with dark eyes that reflected years of hunting experience.', '* Sinding - Final quarry and the werewolf responsible for her death * Fellow Hunters - Professional associates in the pursuit of Sinding * Original Stronghold Family - Distant relations she left behind to pursue her hunting career * Various Jarls and Stewards - Professional contacts who provided bounties', 'Batum worked as a professional hunter and bounty seeker, specializing in tracking and eliminating dangerous creatures and criminals. She operated independently but would occasionally join organized hunting parties for particularly challenging targets.', '* Expert tracker with extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s wilderness * Skilled with both bow and blade, particularly in close-quarters combat * Proficient in survival techniques and wilderness navigation * Advanced knowledge of beast behavior and hunting tactics * Natural Orcish berserker rage abilities', 'Batum spoke in the direct, unembellished manner typical of Orcs, often dropping unnecessary words and speaking in a gravelly tone. Her vocabulary focused on practical matters, particularly hunting and combat terminology.', '* Prove herself as one of Skyrim''s most capable hunters * Build enough wealth to potentially establish her own hunting lodge * Track and eliminate the most dangerous quarries to build her reputation * Earn glory and honor through successful hunts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('beautiful_barbarian', 'The Beautiful Barbarian is a formidable Nord warrior who has made her home in the quiet village of Ivarstead, unaware that she has been marked for death by the Dark Brotherhood. Despite her intimidating presence and martial prowess, she presents a surprisingly weary and casual demeanor that belies her combat capabilities.', 'nord, warrior, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness, she earned her peculiar moniker through a combination of striking Nordic features and exceptional combat skills. After years of mercenary work across the province, she settled in Ivarstead seeking a quieter life, though her reputation as a skilled warrior continues to draw attention - both wanted and unwanted.', 'Though physically imposing and martially skilled, she exhibits a world-weary and somewhat sardonic attitude, often making ironically prophetic statements about her exhaustion. She maintains a casual, approachable demeanor that contrasts with her fearsome reputation, suggesting a desire to distance herself from her violent past.', 'A tall, muscular Nord woman with classical Nordic features including high cheekbones and pale skin. Her years of combat have left her with various battle scars, though they don''t detract from her striking appearance, which earned her the ''beautiful'' portion of her moniker.', '* Vilemyr Inn Staff - Regular patron with cordial relationships * Local Ivarstead Residents - Generally respected but maintains distance * Dark Brotherhood - Unknowing target of their contracts * Former Mercenary Contacts - Distant connections from her previous life', 'Semi-retired mercenary who occasionally takes on local work protecting travelers along the paths near Ivarstead. She supplements her income by helping with security at the Vilemyr Inn during busier periods.', '* Master of two-handed weapon combat, particularly with greatswords * Highly trained in heavy armor combat techniques * Experienced in wilderness survival and tracking * Proficient in intimidation and Nordic battle tactics', 'Speaks in a casual, somewhat ironic manner that often understates her capabilities and current situation. Her Nordic accent is present but softened by years of travel throughout the province.', '* Find a peaceful retirement away from her violent past * Maintain a quiet life in Ivarstead without drawing attention * Eventually save enough gold to purchase property and settle permanently');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('beem-ja', 'Beem-Ja is a deceptive Argonian sorcerer who maintains a faade of caution and wisdom while harboring dark ambitions for power. Initially presenting himself as a thoughtful advisor to his companion Salma, he ultimately reveals himself as a manipulative practitioner of blood magic seeking to absorb the power of ancient Nordic warriors.', 'argonian, mage, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally serving as a retainer to Salma''s wealthy family, Beem-Ja cultivated extensive knowledge of Nordic tombs and ancient magical practices, particularly those involving the transfer of power through blood sacrifice. His studies of Gathrik and Ironbind Barrow likely occurred long before partnering with Salma, suggesting years of careful planning and research into methods of obtaining forbidden power.', 'Beem-Ja presents a calculated exterior of patience and caution, using this persona to mask his true nature as a power-hungry opportunist. He is highly manipulative, willing to form temporary alliances and sacrifice others to achieve his goals. His formal manner of speech and apparent concern for safety serve as tools to gain others'' trust while concealing his true intentions.', 'A tall, lean Argonian with dark green scales and amber eyes that hold an intelligent, calculating gaze. His horns are worn and slightly curved, suggesting middle age, while his movements are precise and deliberate, betraying his magical training.', '* Salma - Adventure companion he secretly plans to sacrifice, maintaining a faade of protective guidance * Salma''s Father - Former employer whom he served while gathering knowledge for his true plans * Gathrik - Ancient Nordic warrior whose power he covets and has extensively studied * Local Mages - Likely maintains distant professional relationships to gather magical knowledge', 'Presents himself as a traveling sorcerer and treasure hunter, though this serves as a cover for his true pursuits in blood magic and power acquisition. Formerly served as an advisor or retainer to Salma''s wealthy family, using the position to further his own studies and ambitions.', '* Accomplished practitioner of Destruction and blood magic * Expert knowledge of Nordic tombs and ancient rituals * Skilled in deception and manipulation * Proficient in defensive magic and ward spells * Advanced understanding of power transfer ceremonies and sacrificial magic', 'Speaks in a formal, measured manner with careful word choice and occasional cryptic statements that hint at his hidden knowledge. His speech patterns reflect both education and calculation, often using respectful titles like ''Miss Salma'' to maintain his faade of propriety.', '* Acquire Gathrik''s power through blood sacrifice * Master forbidden magical practices, particularly those involving power absorption * Increase his magical abilities through whatever means necessary, regardless of moral cost * Potentially seek out other sources of ancient power for similar absorption rituals');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('beirand', 'Beirand is a skilled Nord blacksmith who runs the primary smithy in Solitude, crafting arms and armor for both the Imperial Legion and civilian market. A dedicated family man and loyal citizen of Solitude, he balances his demanding work at the forge with his responsibilities as a husband and father while maintaining high standards of craftsmanship.', 'nord, blacksmith, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Beirand learned the art of blacksmithing from a young age and eventually took over operation of the city''s main smithy. His position became especially crucial during the Civil War, where his skills were vital in supplying the Imperial Legion. He established himself as a respected craftsman and businessman, eventually marrying Sayma and starting a family while maintaining his dedication to serving Solitude.', 'Beirand is hardworking, practical, and straightforward in his dealings with others. He shows unwavering loyalty to Solitude and its leadership, demonstrating a strong sense of civic duty. While generally serious about his work, he displays a warmer, more playful side when interacting with his family and apprentice, though he maintains high professional standards.', 'A sturdy Nord with the muscular build typical of a career blacksmith, featuring callused hands and arms hardened by years at the forge. His face shows the weathering of countless hours working near the heat of the smithy, with subtle burn scars typical of his profession.', '* Sayma - Beloved wife and owner of Bits and Pieces shop * Kayd - Young son whom he''s raising to understand the value of hard work * Heimvar - Apprentice blacksmith he mentors with a mix of strictness and friendly guidance * Imperial Legion - Primary client and source of steady work * Solitude Guard - Regular customers and allies in maintaining city security', 'Master blacksmith operating Solitude''s primary smithy, responsible for crafting and maintaining weapons and armor for both military and civilian clients. He manages all aspects of the business, from procurement of materials to final sales, while also training his apprentice in the trade.', '* Expert-level blacksmithing with specialization in Imperial armor and weapons * Skilled business management and negotiation abilities * Proficient in weapon and armor maintenance and repair * Basic combat training with preference for mace warfare * Knowledge of metallurgy and material properties', 'Speaks in a direct, professional manner with a subtle Nordic accent, often using practical terms related to his trade. His tone shifts between formal business speech with customers and a warmer, more casual manner with family and friends.', '* Maintain the high quality and reputation of Solitude''s smithy while training the next generation * Ensure his family''s financial security and social standing in Solitude * Support Solitude''s defense and prosperity through his craftsmanship * Pass his knowledge and skills to his apprentice Heimvar');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('beitild', 'Beitild is a hard-driving Nord businesswoman who owns and operates the Iron-Breaker Mine in Dawnstar, known for her harsh management style and contentious relationship with her estranged husband. Despite her tough exterior and relentless work ethic, she harbors hidden regrets about her failed marriage and struggles with the supernatural nightmares plaguing the town.', 'nord, blacksmith, pale', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Dawnstar, Beitild worked her way up from a common miner to eventually acquire ownership of Iron-Breaker Mine. Her marriage to Leigelf, owner of the rival Quicksilver Mine, initially united two of Dawnstar''s primary mining operations, but their relationship deteriorated into a bitter business rivalry and personal feud, leading them to live separately despite remaining legally married.', 'Beitild is a stern taskmaster with a brusque, no-nonsense approach to both business and personal relationships. She drives her workers hard and shows little patience for perceived weakness or inefficiency, masking her own emotional vulnerabilities behind a facade of harsh criticism and relentless productivity. Despite her outward hostility toward her husband, unused dialogue suggests she maintains deep-seated feelings for him beneath her bitter exterior.', 'A weathered Nord woman with the muscular build and calloused hands typical of a lifetime of mining work. Her face shows the effects of long hours working in harsh conditions, with premature aging lines from constant exposure to the elements and stress.', '* Leigelf - Estranged husband and rival mine owner with whom she maintains a bitter feud * Karl - Employee at Iron-Breaker Mine who receives frequent harsh criticism * Mine Workers - Subordinates whom she drives hard and often belittles * Jarl Skald the Elder - Local authority figure she acknowledges but maintains minimal interaction with', 'Owner and operator of Iron-Breaker Mine in Dawnstar, where she manages all aspects of the mining operation and personally oversees her workers. She maintains a grueling schedule, working from 6 AM to midnight daily, and handles all business transactions including purchasing ore from independent miners.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of mining operations and ore quality * Capable businesswoman with strong management and entrepreneurial abilities * Physical endurance and strength developed from years of mining work * Basic combat abilities typical of Nord civilians', 'Beitild speaks in a direct, often harsh manner with little concern for social niceties or politeness. Her speech is peppered with mining terminology and dismissive remarks, particularly when referring to her husband or workers.', '* Prove Iron-Breaker Mine''s superiority over the rival Quicksilver Mine * Maintain and increase the mine''s productivity and profitability * Overcome the nightmares plaguing Dawnstar to ensure her workers'' efficiency * Secretly harbors hope of reconciliation with Leigelf, though pride prevents her from acting on it');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('belchimac', 'Belchimac is a bitter and prejudiced Breton miner in Karthwasten who embodies the racial tensions and economic hardships of the Reach. Despite his outward hostility and racist attitudes, he is fundamentally a coward who quickly submits when confronted, revealing deep-seated insecurities and fears about his place in society.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Belchimac has spent his entire adult life working the mines of Karthwasten, witnessing the region''s decline and growing political tensions. His experiences with Nord dominance and the increasing presence of Orcish workers have fostered deep-seated prejudices, while the constant threat of Forsworn activity and Silver-Blood manipulation has left him perpetually anxious and bitter.', 'Belchimac is a deeply pessimistic individual who masks his fears and insecurities with racial prejudice and hostile behavior. He frequently complains about his situation and expresses bigoted views toward Nords and Orcs, yet quickly becomes submissive when confronted, revealing his cowardly nature. His depression and cynicism stem from a genuine belief that his situation is hopeless, leading him to occasionally contemplate joining the Forsworn out of desperation.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with the weathered appearance typical of career miners. His body shows the physical wear of years of hard labor in the mines, with calloused hands and a slightly hunched posture. His face likely bears the premature aging common to those who spend their lives working underground.', '* Ragnar - Fellow miner whom he fears and submits to when confronted * Lash - Orcish miner he discriminates against but fears confrontation with * Enmon - Fellow miner who often discusses their shared troubles * Silver-Blood Family - Views them as oppressors who will eventually enslave the miners', 'Belchimac works as a miner in Sanuarach Mine, performing the physically demanding task of ore extraction. He maintains a regular schedule, working from 8am to 8pm, and resides in the Karthwasten Miner''s Barracks with his fellow workers.', '* Experienced in mining techniques and ore extraction * Basic knowledge of mineral identification * Physical endurance built from years of manual labor * Survival skills necessary for life in the harsh environment of the Reach', 'He speaks in a bitter, complaining tone, often making prejudiced remarks that he quickly retracts when challenged. His speech patterns reveal both his confrontational nature and his underlying cowardice, frequently backpedaling with stuttered apologies when faced with potential consequences.', '* Avoid being sent to Cidhna Mine as a slave * Maintain his position in Sanuarach Mine despite his fears of closure * Find a way to improve his situation, possibly through joining the Forsworn * Survive the political tensions in the Reach without becoming a casualty');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('belethor', 'Belethor is a shrewd and opportunistic Breton merchant who owns the most prominent general goods store in Whiterun. Known for his somewhat unscrupulous business practices and dark humor about selling anyone or anything, he has established himself as a successful albeit morally ambiguous trader in Skyrim''s trading hub.', 'breton, merchant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Belethor moved to Skyrim seeking greater business opportunities in the growing trade center of Whiterun. Through careful networking and aggressive business practices, he managed to secure ownership of a prime retail location in the Plains District, gradually building his reputation as the city''s go-to general goods merchant.', 'Belethor is a calculating and opportunistic businessman who maintains a facade of exaggerated friendliness that barely conceals his mercenary nature. His dark sense of humor, particularly his jokes about selling family members, hints at a moral flexibility that prioritizes profit above all else, though he''s careful to stay within the bounds of law to maintain his respected position in Whiterun society.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with sharp, calculating eyes and weather-worn features typical of merchants who''ve spent years haggling in the marketplace. His well-groomed appearance and straight posture reflect his merchant status, while his hands show the calluses of someone who regularly handles merchandise.', '* Sigurd - His assistant who helps around the shop and can often be heard chopping wood * Ysolda - Business rival who aspires to be a merchant herself * Whiterun Guards - Maintains cordial relationships to ensure shop security * Arcadia - Fellow merchant and occasional business associate * Hulda - Business associate at The Bannered Mare where he sometimes drinks', 'Belethor owns and operates Belethor''s General Goods, the primary general store in Whiterun. He manages all aspects of the business, from procurement and inventory management to sales and customer relations, maintaining regular business hours and handling transactions personally.', '* Expert haggling and mercantile abilities * Keen eye for valuable merchandise and forgeries * Basic accounting and inventory management * Networking and business relationship building * Elementary knowledge of common enchantments for merchandise assessment', 'Speaks with a salesman''s artificial cheerfulness that barely masks his mercenary nature, frequently employing dark humor and sarcasm. His speech is punctuated with frequent references to buying and selling, often making uncomfortable jokes about selling family members.', '* Expand his business influence throughout Whiterun Hold * Accumulate enough wealth to retire comfortably back in High Rock * Maintain his position as Whiterun''s premier general goods merchant * Establish trade connections with other major cities in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('beleval', 'Beleval is a determined Wood Elf who abandoned her bandit past to join the Dawnguard, demonstrating her commitment to protecting Skyrim from the vampire menace. As the only Bosmer member of the vampire hunters, she brings unique archery skills and a fierce dedication to the cause, despite feeling somewhat culturally isolated among the predominantly Nordic organization.', 'woodelf, thief, rift, dawnguard, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Originally operating as a bandit in Skyrim''s wilderness, Beleval likely came from Valenwood seeking opportunity in the harsh northern province. Upon witnessing the growing vampire threat and their predation upon innocent civilians, she abandoned her criminal lifestyle to join Isran''s reformed Dawnguard, seeking redemption through protecting others.', 'Beleval exhibits a strong sense of duty and moral conviction, having turned away from her bandit past to serve a greater cause. Though she openly admits to disliking Isran''s personality, she respects his mission and demonstrates pragmatic loyalty to the Dawnguard''s purpose. She shows particular interest in connecting with other elven members, suggesting a degree of cultural isolation among the predominantly human organization.', 'As a Bosmer, Beleval possesses the characteristic slight build and shorter stature of her race, with the distinctive pointed ears and angular features common to mer. She maintains the athletic physique typical of Wood Elves, built for speed and agility rather than raw strength.', '* Isran - Respected leader despite personal dislike * Fellow Dawnguard members - Professional companions in arms * Other elven visitors - Seeks connection with those sharing her heritage * Vampires - Sworn enemies she has dedicated herself to destroying', 'Beleval serves as a full-time member of the Dawnguard, specializing in crossbow marksmanship and vampire hunting. She maintains a regular schedule of training, patrolling, and standing ready to defend Fort Dawnguard, while also being available for recruitment as both a follower and potential steward.', '* Expert marksman with particular proficiency in crossbow use * Light armor specialist despite wearing heavy armor * Skilled in wilderness survival from her bandit past * Competent with one-handed weapons, particularly war axes * Natural stealth abilities characteristic of Bosmer heritage', 'Beleval speaks with a measured, dutiful tone that reflects her serious commitment to the Dawnguard''s cause. Her dialogue often emphasizes her unique position as the sole Wood Elf among the vampire hunters, while maintaining a professional and determined demeanor.', '* Protect the people of Skyrim from vampire threats * Prove that non-Nords can be just as dedicated to Skyrim''s protection * Redeem her past bandit lifestyle through honorable service * Master the unique combat techniques of the Dawnguard');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('belrand', 'Belrand is a versatile Nord mercenary who has mastered both martial combat and magical arts, making him a rare spellsword in Skyrim''s harsh environment. His practical approach to survival and combat has earned him a reputation as a reliable sword-for-hire in Solitude, where he offers his unique combination of skills to potential employers.', 'nord, mage, haafingar, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Belrand broke from the typical Nord distrust of magic, choosing to study both martial and arcane arts from an early age. He likely received training from the College of Winterhold while also honing his combat skills through practical experience as a sellsword. His unconventional path has led him to settle in Solitude, where the cosmopolitan atmosphere is more accepting of his hybrid fighting style.', 'Belrand is pragmatic and adaptable, valuing versatility above specialization. He maintains a jovial and enthusiastic attitude toward adventure, showing genuine excitement about discovering new dangers and wonders. His practical approach to combining magic and melee combat reflects a mind unbound by traditional Nord prejudices against magic.', 'Belrand is a sturdy Nord male with the characteristic strong build of his race, though perhaps slightly leaner than the typical Nord warrior due to his split focus between physical and magical training. His face shows the weathering of countless adventures, with battle scars that tell tales of his mercenary work.', '* Corpulus Vinius - Professional acquaintance and innkeeper who provides him lodging at the Winking Skeever * Regular patrons of the Winking Skeever - Casual relationships maintained through his permanent residence * College of Winterhold - Loose connections from his presumed magical training * Various merchants in Solitude - Business relationships built through his mercenary work', 'Belrand works as a freelance mercenary, specifically marketing himself as a spellsword-for-hire from his base at the Winking Skeever in Solitude. His services combine the roles of traditional sellsword and battle-mage, offering potential employers greater versatility than typical Nordic warriors.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat, particularly with short blades * Skilled in Alteration magic, specifically protective spells like Oakflesh * Capable practitioner of Conjuration, able to summon familiars in battle * Adept at Restoration magic, including healing and ward spells * Experienced in light armor combat techniques', 'Belrand speaks with confidence and enthusiasm, often emphasizing the practical advantages of his diverse skill set. His speech patterns reflect both formal magical training and mercenary pragmatism, frequently using analogies that compare spell and blade.', '* Build a reputation as Skyrim''s premier spellsword-for-hire * Prove that the combination of magic and martial prowess is superior to either alone * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually establish his own combat training school * Challenge and overcome the Nordic cultural bias against magic use');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('belyn_hlaalu', 'Belyn Hlaalu is a determined Dark Elf farmer who has carved out a respectable living in the harsh climate of Windhelm despite the racial prejudices he faces. He embodies the philosophy that actions speak louder than words, choosing to prove his worth through agricultural success rather than dwelling on discrimination.', 'darkelf, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born to the prestigious House Hlaalu of Morrowind, Belyn likely fled to Skyrim following the Red Year and the subsequent Argonian invasion. Despite his noble heritage, he chose to rebuild his life through honest labor, establishing one of the few successful farms in Windhelm''s unforgiving climate.', 'Pragmatic and hardworking, Belyn believes in earning respect through actions rather than words or complaints. He maintains a stern but fair demeanor with his workers and takes pride in his agricultural achievements. Though he faces discrimination in Windhelm, he channels his frustrations into productive work rather than bitter resentment.', 'A weathered Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, showing signs of age and hard labor. His sturdy frame and calloused hands reflect years of agricultural work, while his posture remains proud despite the physical demands of farming.', '* Adisla - His Nord employee, maintains a professional but occasionally friendly relationship * Captain Lonely-Gale - Shows particular interest in the retired ship''s captain, possibly admiring his status * Endario - Business contact who supplies frostwheat, though their relationship appears strained * Local Nord Community - Strives to earn their respect through demonstrable hard work * Dark Elf Community - Somewhat distant, disapproves of their tendency to complain about conditions', 'Owner and operator of Hlaalu Farm, one of the few successful agricultural operations in Windhelm''s harsh climate. He manages all aspects of the farm''s operation, from crop selection to harvest scheduling, while also handling business negotiations for supplies and crop sales.', '* Expert knowledge of agriculture and crop management in harsh climates * Business acumen and negotiation skills developed through farm management * Physical endurance and strength from years of agricultural labor * Leadership and personnel management experience * Advanced understanding of wheat cultivation and harvest timing', 'Direct and authoritative in his speech, often using a matter-of-fact tone that reflects his no-nonsense approach to life. He frequently employs practical metaphors and agricultural references, speaking with the slight accent characteristic of Morrowind natives.', '* Establish Hlaalu Farm as the most successful agricultural operation in Windhelm * Earn the respect and acceptance of the Nord community through demonstrable success * Prove that Dark Elves can prosper through hard work rather than complaints * Expand his farming operation and possibly employ more workers * Maintain his family name''s dignity despite changed circumstances');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bendt', 'Bendt is a reclusive Imperial chef who serves as the head cook at the Bards College in Solitude, known for his stern demeanor and unwavering dedication to his craft. Despite his generally antisocial nature, he shows a rare glimpse of warmth during the annual Burning of King Olaf festival, where he eagerly shares his specially-made confections with festival-goers.', 'imperial, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Originally trained in the Imperial City''s culinary arts, Bendt made his way to Skyrim seeking a position that would allow him to practice his craft in relative solitude. After years of working in busy taverns and noble houses, he found his ideal role in the Bards College, where he could maintain strict control over his kitchen domain with minimal social interaction.', 'Bendt is a perfectionist who values order and routine above all else, displaying clear irritation when his carefully maintained kitchen sanctuary is disturbed by uninvited visitors. Though outwardly gruff and antisocial, he takes immense pride in his culinary work and harbors a hidden artistic side that emerges during festival celebrations.', 'A tall, elderly Imperial with weathered features and callused hands from decades of cooking. His face bears the deep creases of someone who frequently frowns, though laugh lines around his eyes suggest a capacity for joy rarely seen by others.', '* Viarmo - Professional relationship with the Headmaster, who respects Bendt''s desire for solitude * College Students - Generally antagonistic, viewing them as intrusive disruptions to his routine * Kitchen Staff - Minimal interaction, preferring to work alone * Evette San - Unknown connection, possibly a former acquaintance due to mysteriously having her house key', 'As head cook of the Bards College, Bendt is responsible for preparing all meals for the institution''s students and faculty. He maintains strict control over the kitchen''s operations and inventory, personally overseeing every aspect of meal preparation and service.', '* Master-level cooking abilities with expertise in both Nordic and Imperial cuisine * Exceptional knowledge of ingredients and their proper storage * Skilled at confectionery, particularly evident in his festival treats * Basic combat training with daggers for kitchen work and self-defense * Expert-level organizational and inventory management abilities', 'Bendt speaks in short, direct sentences with a gruff Imperial accent, often delivering his words with a dismissive or irritated tone. His vocabulary is practical and unembellished, though he occasionally uses culinary terminology when discussing his work.', '* Maintain absolute control and order within his kitchen domain * Perfect his festival candy recipes for the annual Burning of King Olaf celebration * Keep students and other unwanted visitors from disturbing his carefully maintained routine * Preserve the traditional cooking methods he learned in Cyrodiil');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('benor', 'Benor is a self-appointed guardian of Morthal who, despite lacking official guard status, takes it upon himself to protect the town and its inhabitants. A proud Nord warrior with aspirations of becoming a full-fledged guard, he maintains a vigilant watch over the settlement while harboring deep suspicions about both the Jarl''s leadership and the mysterious wizard Falion.', 'nord, warrior, hjaalmarch, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Morthal, Benor developed his combat skills through years of self-training and dealing with the harsh environment of Hjaalmarch. Having witnessed the decline of Morthal''s security and the growing tensions within the town, he took it upon himself to assist the guard despite lacking official appointment, earning him a unofficial position and sleeping privileges in the guardhouse.', 'Benor is prideful and territorial, quick to challenge others to prove his fighting prowess. He shows a strong sense of duty to Morthal despite his criticism of its leadership, demonstrating both loyalty and independent thinking. His suspicious nature, particularly toward magic users and the Jarl''s passive governance, reveals a conservative Nord mindset that favors traditional warrior values.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the characteristic robust build of his race, bearing numerous small scars from his years of combat and training. His weathered face and calloused hands speak to his life of physical labor and combat, while his vigilant posture reflects his self-appointed guardian role.', '* Gorm - Close friend and drinking companion at the Moorside Inn * Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - Distrusts her leadership and passive approach to town security * Falion - Harbors deep suspicion of the court wizard and his magical practices * Local Guards - Maintains a cooperative but unofficial relationship with the regular guard force', 'Benor serves as an unofficial auxiliary to Morthal''s guard force, performing regular patrols and investigating disturbances without formal recognition or pay. His self-appointed duties include patrolling the town bridges, investigating the mysterious burned house, and maintaining a watchful eye over the community.', '* Proficient in heavy armor combat and two-handed weapon techniques * Experienced in guard duties and patrol tactics * Skilled brawler with strong hand-to-hand combat abilities * Basic investigation skills developed through unofficial guard work', 'Speaks in a direct, assertive manner typical of Nord warriors, often making bold claims about his fighting abilities. His speech patterns reflect both pride in his abilities and frustration with the current state of Morthal''s governance.', '* Obtain official recognition and appointment as a full-fledged guard of Morthal * Protect Morthal from both external threats and internal magical influences * Prove himself as the settlement''s most capable warrior * Help restore Morthal to its former peaceful state');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bergritte_battle-born', 'Bergritte Battle-Born is a dignified matriarch of one of Whiterun''s most prominent noble families, embodying traditional Nord values while navigating the complex political landscape of the civil war. As a devoted grandmother and keeper of family traditions, she maintains a delicate balance between preserving her clan''s prestigious status and protecting her loved ones during tumultuous times.', 'nord, noble, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born into Nord nobility, Bergritte married into the Battle-Born clan in her youth, helping to maintain their position as one of Whiterun''s most influential families. She has witnessed the rise and fall of the relationship between the Battle-Borns and Gray-Manes, from generations of friendship to bitter rivalry during the civil war, shaping her current worldview and political stance.', 'Bergritte is a proud, traditional Nord woman who combines maternal warmth with aristocratic dignity. She shows particular concern for her grandson Lars while maintaining the family''s strong Imperial allegiance, often expressing disdain for the Stormcloaks and Gray-Manes. Despite her conservative nature, she displays a surprising wit and appreciation for literature, even making occasional ribald jokes about books like ''The Lusty Argonian Maid.''', 'An elderly Nord woman with the bearing of nobility, showing signs of age but maintaining a dignified posture. Her face bears the wrinkles of wisdom and experience, with sharp, observant eyes that reflect her attention to both family matters and city politics. Her movements are deliberate and graceful, befitting her status as a family matriarch.', '* Olfrid Battle-Born - Husband and patriarch of the clan * Jon Battle-Born - Son, whom she worries about due to his secret romance with Olfina Gray-Mane * Alfhild Battle-Born - Daughter and frequent reading companion * Idolaf Battle-Born - Son-in-law * Lars Battle-Born - Beloved grandson whom she fiercely protects * Gray-Mane Family - Former friends turned rivals due to civil war tensions', 'Bergritte serves as the matriarch of Clan Battle-Born, managing household affairs and maintaining the family''s social standing in Whiterun. Her daily routine involves overseeing domestic matters, participating in social gatherings, and ensuring the family''s traditions and values are preserved for future generations.', '* Accomplished in household management and maintaining noble social protocols * Knowledgeable about literature and Nord traditions * Skilled in social navigation and maintaining political alliances * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Experienced in child-rearing and family counseling', 'Bergritte speaks with the refined accent of Nord nobility, tempering her formal tone with occasional warmth when addressing family members. Her vocabulary reflects her educated background, though she can be sharp-tongued when discussing political opponents or the Gray-Manes.', '* Maintain the Battle-Born clan''s prominence and influence in Whiterun * Protect her grandson Lars from both physical threats and social hardships * Support the Imperial cause while preserving family safety during the civil war * Restore the Battle-Born name to its former glory after the political strife ends');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bersi_honey-hand', 'Bersi Honey-Hand is a principled Nord shopkeeper and former sailor who maintains a general goods store in Riften while trying to stand against the city''s endemic corruption. Despite his moral convictions and religious devotion to Mara, he finds himself caught between his ideals and the harsh realities of doing business in a city dominated by the Thieves Guild.', 'nord, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a sailor who owned and operated a fishing vessel called the Brawny Prawn, Bersi eventually sold his boat and established himself as a merchant in Riften. His transition from seafaring to shopkeeping represents his desire for a more stable life, though his choice of settling in Riften has brought its own challenges.', 'Bersi is stubborn and principled, maintaining strong moral convictions despite living in Riften''s corrupt environment. He genuinely believes in the power of prayer and worship at the Temple of Mara to improve society, showing an idealistic streak that many consider naive. While initially defiant against criminal elements, he ultimately shows pragmatism when faced with real threats to his livelihood.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered features typical of someone who spent years at sea. His hands are calloused from his sailing days, though now somewhat softened by merchant work. His face likely shows signs of aging and stress from dealing with Riften''s harsh business environment.', '* Drifa - His loving and supportive wife who helps run The Pawned Prawn * Thieves Guild - Antagonistic relationship as they extort protection money from him * Temple of Mara - Devoted worshipper and supporter * Other Riften Merchants - Generally cordial relationships, though some mock his religious solutions to corruption', 'Bersi owns and operates The Pawned Prawn, a general goods store in Riften. He manages inventory, handles transactions, and maintains his shop''s reputation as a legitimate business despite pressure from criminal elements. His daily routine involves long hours of shopkeeping interspersed with meals and evening market visits.', '* Experienced sailor with knowledge of navigation and seamanship * Capable merchant with business administration abilities * Basic combat proficiency with daggers * Trading and bartering expertise * Religious knowledge, particularly regarding the teachings of Mara', 'Bersi speaks with the direct, honest manner of a merchant who values straightforward communication. His speech often reflects his moral convictions and religious beliefs, though he can become defensive when confronted about protection payments.', '* Maintain a successful legitimate business despite Riften''s corrupt environment * Help improve Riften''s moral character through religious devotion and example * Eventually free himself from the Thieves Guild''s influence * Preserve his dignity and principles while surviving in a challenging business climate');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('betrid_silver-blood', 'Betrid Silver-Blood is a wealthy Nord noblewoman who married into one of Markarth''s most powerful families purely for financial gain. She represents the height of Markarth''s privileged elite, maintaining a carefully cultivated image of superiority while harboring deep resentment over her husband''s perceived lack of ambition.', 'nord, noble, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born into Markarth''s upper class, Betrid was raised with expectations of wealth and status. She strategically pursued and married Thonar Silver-Blood specifically for his family''s vast wealth and influence, though their marriage has become increasingly strained due to power struggles within the Silver-Blood family. Her life of privilege has shaped her into a woman who values wealth and status above all else.', 'Betrid is openly elitist and condescending, taking pride in flaunting her status and wealth while looking down on those she considers beneath her station. She is remarkably frank about her materialistic motivations, showing no shame in admitting she married for money. Despite her privileged position, she harbors frustration over her husband''s reluctance to seize more power within his family, revealing an ambitious and manipulative nature.', 'A well-maintained Nord woman with features softened by a life of luxury and leisure. Her appearance reflects her wealthy status, with smooth, unmarked hands that have never known manual labor. She carries herself with practiced poise and maintains the groomed appearance expected of Markarth''s elite.', '* Thonar Silver-Blood - Husband of convenience, whom she openly admits to marrying for money * Thongvor Silver-Blood - Brother-in-law and head of the Silver-Blood family, whom she views as an obstacle to her husband''s advancement * Treasury House Staff - Servants whom she treats with consistent disdain * Markarth''s Elite - Social peers whom she maintains careful relationships with to preserve her status', 'As the wife of Thonar Silver-Blood, Betrid''s primary role is maintaining her social status and representing the Silver-Blood family''s interests in Markarth''s upper-class society. She spends her days engaged in leisure activities at the Treasury House, particularly reading and socializing with other members of Markarth''s elite.', '* Expert in social manipulation and political maneuvering * Knowledgeable in literature and reading, as evidenced by her daily activities * Proficient in maintaining high-society appearances and etiquette * Basic self-defense capabilities, carrying an iron dagger for protection', 'Betrid speaks in a haughty, condescending tone that emphasizes her perceived superiority over others. Her vocabulary and manner of speech reflect her upper-class upbringing, often using dismissive or belittling language when addressing those she considers beneath her.', '* Pressure Thonar into taking control of the Silver-Blood family from his brother Thongvor * Maintain and elevate her social status within Markarth''s elite society * Secure greater wealth and influence for herself through her marriage to Thonar * Preserve her comfortable lifestyle of luxury and leisure');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('big_laborer', 'The Big Laborer is a hardworking Nord farmhand at Katla''s Farm near Solitude who takes immense pride in his agricultural duties. Known for his imposing physical presence and short temper, he represents the strong work ethic typical of Nord laborers while harboring a deep resentment toward interruptions that stems from past experiences.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born to a family of farmers outside Solitude, he learned the value of hard work from an early age. After losing his own farm during the Civil War, he found employment at Katla''s Farm, where his impressive strength and farming expertise made him an invaluable worker, though the loss of his independence left him with a bitter outlook.', 'The Big Laborer is a gruff, irritable individual who values solitude and uninterrupted work above all else. His short temper and hostile responses to strangers mask a deep-seated frustration with his current station in life, having once been an independent farmer himself. Despite his intimidating demeanor, he maintains a strong work ethic and sense of duty to his employer.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with weathered skin from years of outdoor labor. His large, calloused hands and broad shoulders reflect his life of physical work, while his imposing stature makes him stand out among other farmhands. Multiple scars from farming accidents mark his arms and hands.', '* Katla - Employer who values his work ethic despite his attitude * Farm Workers - Maintains minimal but professional relationships with colleagues * Solitude Guards - Occasional tension due to his aggressive demeanor * Local Merchants - Strained relationships due to his unwillingness to engage in pleasant conversation', 'Works as the primary laborer at Katla''s Farm, responsible for the heaviest and most demanding agricultural tasks. His duties include plowing fields, harvesting crops, and maintaining farm equipment, tasks that require his considerable strength and farming expertise.', '* Exceptional physical strength suited for heavy agricultural labor * Expert knowledge of farming techniques and crop management * Proficient in tool maintenance and basic carpentry * Basic combat abilities typical of Nord warriors * Advanced animal handling skills', 'Speaks in short, irritated bursts with a thick Nordic accent, often ending conversations abruptly. His vocabulary is simple but direct, reflecting his no-nonsense attitude and preference for solitude.', '* Save enough money to eventually purchase his own farm again * Maintain his reputation as an efficient and reliable worker despite his poor social skills * Avoid unnecessary social interaction while performing his duties * Perfect his farming techniques to increase crop yields');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('birna', 'Birna is a hardworking Nord shopkeeper struggling to maintain her small business, Birna''s Oddments, in the declining town of Winterhold. She shoulders the burden of supporting both herself and her alcoholic brother through her modest trading operation, displaying remarkable resilience despite the challenging circumstances.', 'nord, merchant, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Winterhold, Birna witnessed the city''s decline following the Great Collapse, which transformed the once-prosperous capital into a shadow of its former self. She inherited the family shop and took on the responsibility of supporting her brother Ranmir after their parents'' passing, watching helplessly as he descended into alcoholism following his girlfriend Isabella''s disappearance.', 'Practical and world-weary, Birna approaches life with a stark realism born from years of struggle. While maintaining a strong work ethic, she harbors deep frustration over her brother''s self-destructive behavior and the town''s declining state, often expressing her feelings through sardonic observations and blunt honesty. Despite her pessimistic outlook, she continues to persevere through difficult circumstances.', 'A Nord woman of average height with the characteristic hardy build of her race, showing signs of stress and weariness on her face. Her hands are rough from years of handling merchandise, and she carries herself with the steady, practical bearing of a merchant used to long hours of standing.', '* Ranmir - Her alcoholic brother whom she reluctantly supports despite his destructive behavior * Thaena - Her only regular customer, though their relationship is strained and purely transactional * Isabella - Her brother''s missing girlfriend whose disappearance contributed to the family''s troubles * College of Winterhold - Maintains a distant but necessary business relationship with the institution''s members', 'Birna owns and operates Birna''s Oddments, a general goods store in Winterhold, where she trades in various items and curiosities. She manages all aspects of the business single-handedly, from procurement to sales, working long hours to maintain the shop''s viability in the sparsely populated town.', '* Experienced trader with knowledge of merchandise value and bartering * Practical knowledge of various goods and their uses * Basic accounting and business management abilities * Survival skills necessary for living in Winterhold''s harsh climate', 'Birna speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a slight Nordic accent, often peppering her speech with cynical observations about her situation. Her tone is generally weary but professional, though it can become sharp when discussing her brother''s drinking habits.', '* Maintain a sustainable income to support herself and her brother despite Winterhold''s declining economy * Find a way to help her brother overcome his alcoholism * Expand her customer base beyond the few remaining residents of Winterhold * Eventually save enough money to possibly relocate to a more prosperous town');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bjartur', 'Bjartur is a defiant Nord prisoner held in Castle Dour Dungeon for her unwavering support of the Stormcloak rebellion. A passionate advocate for Skyrim''s independence, she maintains her fierce loyalty to Ulfric''s cause even while facing potential execution, embodying the stubborn resilience and pride characteristic of her Nord heritage.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim during the growing tensions between the Empire and its people, Bjartur likely came from a traditional Nord family that resented Imperial control. She joined the Stormcloak cause early in the rebellion, though was eventually captured during operations in Haafingar Hold and imprisoned in Solitude''s Castle Dour.', 'Bjartur exhibits fierce pride and unwavering loyalty to the Stormcloak cause, refusing to break under Imperial imprisonment. She is confrontational and politically aware, often engaging in heated debates about Imperial politics and challenging her captors'' allegiances. Despite facing execution, she maintains a defiant spirit and sharp wit, using her words as weapons when physical ones are denied to her.', 'As a Nord female, Bjartur likely possesses the characteristic hardy build and fair complexion common to her race. Years of potential military service with the Stormcloaks would have left her physically fit, though her time in prison may have begun to take its toll.', '* Ahtar - Antagonistic relationship with her jailor, frequently engaging in political debates * Imperial Guards - Views them with contempt as representatives of Imperial oppression * Stormcloak Rebels - Maintains strong loyalty to her fellow soldiers and the cause * Ulfric Stormcloak - Shows deep devotion to his leadership and vision for Skyrim', 'Currently a prisoner in Castle Dour Dungeon, though her previous role was likely as an active Stormcloak soldier or supporter. Her knowledge of politics and Imperial policies suggests she may have held a position of some responsibility within the rebellion.', '* Skilled in political debate and rhetoric * Likely trained in combat as a Stormcloak soldier * Mental fortitude and resistance to interrogation * Knowledge of Imperial and Stormcloak political affairs', 'Bjartur speaks with aggressive defiance, using sharp, confrontational language filled with Nordic colloquialisms and insults like ''horker.'' Her tone is bitter and sardonic when addressing Imperials, but passionate when discussing Skyrim''s independence.', '* Maintain loyalty to the Stormcloak cause despite imprisonment * Resist Imperial interrogation attempts * Survive imprisonment while holding true to her beliefs * See Skyrim freed from Imperial control, even if she doesn''t live to witness it');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bjorlam', 'Bjorlam is a seasoned Nord carriage driver who serves as one of Whiterun''s primary transportation providers, connecting the hold capital to other major cities across Skyrim. His years of experience traversing Skyrim''s dangerous roads have made him not only an expert navigator but also a valuable source of local knowledge and information.', 'nord, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun Hold, Bjorlam learned the carriage trade from his father, who served the hold before him. He has spent decades traversing Skyrim''s roads, surviving numerous bandit attacks and harsh weather conditions, which helped him develop both combat skills and extensive knowledge of the province''s geography and politics.', 'Bjorlam is a friendly and talkative individual who enjoys sharing his knowledge with travelers, particularly about his beloved home city of Whiterun. He maintains a professional demeanor while being approachable and helpful, demonstrating both Nord pride and pragmatic business sense in his dealings with customers.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with weather-worn features that speak to decades spent on the open road. His muscular build reflects both his Nordic heritage and the physical demands of managing horses and defending his carriage from threats.', '* Skulvar Sable-Hilt - Fellow businessman at Whiterun Stables with whom he coordinates services * Bannered Mare Staff - Regular contacts who help him stay informed about city gossip and travelers'' needs * Other Carriage Drivers - Maintains cordial professional relationships with drivers from other holds * Battle-Borns and Gray-Manes - Maintains neutrality in their feud while being well-informed about both families', 'Bjorlam operates as Whiterun''s primary carriage driver, providing essential transportation services between major cities. His role extends beyond mere transportation to include being an informal source of information for travelers and maintaining one of the vital commercial links between Skyrim''s holds.', '* Experienced horseman and carriage driver capable of navigating Skyrim''s challenging terrain * Competent warrior skilled with an iron war axe for defending against road bandits * Extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s geography and safe travel routes * Strong interpersonal skills and deep knowledge of local politics and customs', 'Speaks in a warm, friendly manner with the characteristic Nordic accent, often offering helpful advice and local information unprompted. His speech patterns reflect both his professional customer service orientation and traditional Nord straightforwardness.', '* Maintain a profitable and reliable transportation service connecting Whiterun to other holds * Preserve his reputation as a trustworthy source of local information and safe passage * Eventually pass his business and knowledge to an apprentice who can carry on the tradition');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bjornolfr', 'Bjornolfr was a Nord farmer and amateur conjurer who maintained a secret romantic relationship with Hrodulf while living in Solitude. His deep love and concern for Hrodulf ultimately led him to follow his partner to Solstheim, where he met a tragic end in a hidden Dwemer chamber.', 'nord, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally from Solitude, Bjornolfr lived a relatively quiet life as a farmer while secretly studying the art of Conjuration. He developed a romantic relationship with Hrodulf, keeping their partnership private due to social pressures. When Hrodulf became obsessed with Dwemer technology and moved to Solstheim, Bjornolfr maintained contact through letters before making the fatal decision to follow him.', 'Bjornolfr was a deeply caring and loyal individual, willing to risk everything for those he loved. His letters reveal a cautious and thoughtful nature, balanced with determination and unwavering devotion. Despite his concerns about Hrodulf''s growing obsession with Dwemer technology, he remained supportive and protective of their relationship.', 'A typical Nord male with the characteristic sturdy build of his race, likely weathered from years of farming work. His hands would have shown the calluses of agricultural labor, though his study of magic may have given him a slightly more scholarly bearing than the average farmer.', '* Hrodulf - Romantic partner and primary relationship, shared a deep emotional bond * Solitude Farmers - Professional acquaintances who likely knew little of his personal life * College of Winterhold - Possible distant connection due to his interest in Conjuration magic * Local Merchants - Business relationships for selling crops', 'Bjornolfr was primarily a farmer in Solitude, cultivating crops and selling his harvest to local markets. He supplemented this practical work with the study of Conjuration magic, though likely kept this pursuit private from most of his acquaintances.', '* Basic farming techniques and agricultural knowledge * Novice-level Conjuration magic abilities * Literacy and letter-writing capabilities, unusual for a common farmer * Basic combat training with daggers, typical of Nord culture', 'Based on his letter writing, Bjornolfr spoke with care and consideration, using direct but emotionally honest language. His vocabulary would have reflected both his farming background and his magical studies, creating an interesting mix of practical and arcane terminology.', '* Reunite with Hrodulf and ensure his safety and well-being * Develop his understanding of Conjuration magic while maintaining his farming life * Build a stable future with Hrodulf away from societal judgment * Understand the Dwemer technology that so fascinated his partner');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('black-briar_mercenary', 'A hardened professional soldier-for-hire employed by the influential Black-Briar family to protect their interests and properties in Riften. Though technically a mercenary, they operate more like a private security force, maintaining strict discipline and unwavering loyalty to Maven Black-Briar''s criminal empire.', 'warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally trained as a guard in Cyrodiil, they found better pay and opportunities in Skyrim''s mercenary trade. After proving their worth in several smaller contracts, they caught the attention of Maven Black-Briar, who offered steady employment protecting her family''s interests. Years of service have earned them a trusted position within the Black-Briar organization''s security hierarchy.', 'Stern and professional with an unwavering sense of duty to their employer. Shows little emotion or personal investment beyond their contracted obligations, but maintains a fierce loyalty to fellow mercenaries in their unit. Approaches all situations with calculated pragmatism, willing to use whatever level of force necessary to achieve their objectives.', 'Muscular and battle-hardened with numerous scars from years of combat service. Stands slightly above average height with a rigid military posture that betrays their formal guard training. Weather-beaten features and calloused hands speak to countless hours of outdoor patrol duty.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Employer and commander, respected and feared in equal measure * Fellow Black-Briar Mercenaries - Tight-knit brotherhood forged through shared duty * Riften Guard - Professional rivalry but mutual understanding * Thieves Guild - Cautious cooperation due to Maven''s alliance * Maven''s Enemies - Treated as hostile threats to be eliminated', 'Serves as an elite private security officer for the Black-Briar family, responsible for protecting their properties and interests through armed force. Duties include guarding the Black-Briar Lodge, escorting valuable shipments, and eliminating threats to the family''s operations.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Proficient with multiple weapon types including sword, bow, and battleaxe * Trained in guard tactics and patrol procedures * Skilled in intimidation and threat assessment * Basic knowledge of Nordic customs and criminal operations', 'Speaks in clipped, authoritative tones with a slight Imperial accent, favoring direct threats and commands over conversation. Uses minimal words to convey maximum intimidation, often punctuating statements with aggressive body language.', '* Maintain position of trust within the Black-Briar organization * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually retire comfortably * Protect the reputation and interests of the Black-Briar family * Advance to a leadership position among the mercenary force');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('blasphemous_priest', 'A tormented Nord priest who has turned to the Dark Brotherhood in desperation, residing in Whiterun''s Temple of Kynareth while harboring dark secrets. Despite his holy occupation, he has performed the Black Sacrament, marking him as someone willing to embrace darkness to achieve his ends.', 'nord, priest, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally trained as a proper priest of Kynareth, he experienced a profound crisis of faith after witnessing events that shook his religious convictions. His descent into darkness began gradually, starting with small compromises that eventually led him to embrace forbidden knowledge and ultimately perform the Black Sacrament, though he maintains his priestly facade to avoid suspicion.', 'Outwardly projects the demeanor of a dedicated priest while internally struggling with moral corruption and religious doubt. His interactions are marked by an underlying tension between his public persona and private desperation, often speaking in cryptic religious metaphors that mask darker meanings. Shows signs of paranoia and obsession regarding his intended target.', 'A tall, gaunt Nord male with deep-set eyes and hollow cheeks that suggest recent weight loss from stress or illness. His pale complexion and dark circles under his eyes indicate many sleepless nights, while his slightly trembling hands betray his inner turmoil.', '* Temple of Kynareth - Maintains a strained relationship with fellow priests who sense something amiss * Danica Pure-Spring - Superior at the temple who has growing suspicions about his behavior * Dark Brotherhood - Secret contact through the Black Sacrament * Unknown Target - Object of his murderous intentions, identity varies', 'Serves as a priest in the Temple of Kynareth, performing healing rituals and offering religious guidance to visitors. Secretly maintains correspondence with the Dark Brotherhood while continuing his religious duties as a cover for his true intentions.', '* Adept-level Restoration magic used in healing rituals * Knowledge of religious rites and ceremonies * Proficiency with ritual daggers and basic weapon skills * Expert-level knowledge of religious texts and temple protocols', 'Speaks in a measured, priestly tone that occasionally breaks to reveal underlying desperation and darkness. Frequently weaves religious terminology into conversation while giving it sinister double meanings.', '* Eliminate his chosen target through the Dark Brotherhood contract * Maintain his position at the temple without arousing suspicion * Reconcile his religious beliefs with his dark actions * Eventually escape Whiterun once his deed is done');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('blood_horker', 'A hardened member of the notorious Blood Horker pirates who terrorize the northern coastlines of Skyrim during the Civil War. Operating from their hidden base at Japhet''s Folly, they represent a fierce blend of traditional piracy and magical combat prowess, maintaining a secret alliance with Clan Shatter-Shield to control maritime trade.', 'thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a common bandit who found greater purpose and profit in maritime raiding, this Blood Horker joined the crew under Captain Stig Salt-Plank''s leadership. Through proving their worth in numerous raids and showing loyalty to Haldyn''s vision, they earned their place among the feared pirate crew that controls the Sea of Ghosts.', 'Aggressive and confrontational, with an unwavering loyalty to both Captain Haldyn and the Blood Horker cause. Shows a ruthless efficiency in combat and raiding operations, yet maintains a sense of honor among thieves, strictly adhering to the agreements made with Clan Shatter-Shield.', 'Weather-beaten and scarred from years of seafaring and combat, with calloused hands and sea-hardened muscles. Bears the distinctive markings and tattoos common among Blood Horkers, with skin tanned and roughened by constant exposure to the harsh northern elements.', '* Haldyn - Respected battlemage leader and commander * Stig Salt-Plank - Direct captain and tactical superior * Clan Shatter-Shield - Secret business partners and protected allies * Suvaris Atheron - Key contact for coordinating protected shipping routes * East Empire Company - Primary targets and sworn enemies * Fellow Blood Horkers - Trusted brothers-in-arms', 'Serves as both a maritime raider and defender of Japhet''s Folly, participating in ship attacks and protecting their hidden fortress. Alternates between naval warfare and land-based operations, often acting as part of coordinated strikes against merchant vessels.', '* Proficient in maritime combat and ship-to-ship warfare tactics * Experienced in both physical combat and basic magical abilities * Expert navigator familiar with the treacherous waters of the Sea of Ghosts * Skilled in survival techniques for the harsh northern climate * Capable of coordinating with both warrior and mage companions in battle', 'Speaks in a gruff, traditional pirate dialect peppered with nautical terminology and threatening declarations. Frequently employs classic pirate phrases like ''Yarr!'' and ''Avast!'' while making threats or engaging in combat.', '* Maintain and expand Blood Horker control over northern shipping routes * Protect the secrecy of Japhet''s Folly and their arrangement with Clan Shatter-Shield * Accumulate personal wealth through successful raiding operations * Earn greater recognition and status within the Blood Horker hierarchy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bodil', 'Bodil is a dedicated Nord miner who has made Iron-Breaker Mine both her workplace and permanent home, embodying the Nordic values of hard work and perseverance. She represents the backbone of Dawnstar''s mining economy, maintaining an almost monastic dedication to her work that sees her never leaving the mine''s depths.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born into a mining family in the Pale, Bodil likely learned the trade from an early age, as is common among Nord mining communities. She chose to fully dedicate herself to the mining life, eventually finding employment under Beitild at Iron-Breaker Mine where she made the unusual decision to live permanently within the mine itself, suggesting possible past traumas or losses that led her to seek solace in simple, focused work.', 'Bodil is remarkably stoic and single-minded, displaying an almost ascetic dedication to her work that borders on obsessive. She exhibits a pragmatic, no-nonsense attitude toward life, showing little interest in matters beyond her immediate duties and maintaining a simple, structured existence that revolves entirely around her work in the mine.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the muscular build typical of someone who spends their days wielding a pickaxe. Her hands are calloused from years of mining, and her skin likely bears the pale pallor of someone who rarely sees sunlight, while her frame shows the physical conditioning that comes from constant physical labor.', '* Beitild - Employer and mine owner, maintains a purely professional relationship * Gjak - Fellow miner and only regular companion, shares similar dedication to mining life * Iron-Breaker Mine - Shows an almost spiritual connection to her workplace * Dawnstar Community - Maintains minimal connections with the surface world', 'Bodil works as a full-time miner at Iron-Breaker Mine, where she performs the physically demanding task of extracting iron ore from the mine''s depths. Unlike most miners who return home after their shifts, she has fully integrated her life into the mine, making it both her workplace and permanent residence.', '* Expert-level mining abilities and ore identification * Physical endurance and strength from constant mining work * Basic survival skills necessary for living in a mine * Practical knowledge of mining safety and cave navigation', 'Bodil speaks in terse, direct statements, using minimal words to convey her thoughts. Her manner of speech reflects her no-nonsense personality, often limiting conversations to practical matters related to mining work.', '* Maintain consistent ore production in Iron-Breaker Mine * Preserve her simple, structured life focused on mining * Continue providing valuable resources for Dawnstar''s economy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('boethiah_cultist', 'A devoted Dunmer cultist who serves as one of Boethiah''s most fervent followers at the Sacellum of Boethiah. She embodies the Prince''s aspects of deceit, conspiracy, and treachery while acting as a recruiter and teacher for new initiates seeking to prove themselves worthy of Boethiah''s attention.', 'eastmarch, daedric', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born into a traditional Dunmer family in Morrowind, she rejected the Tribunal faith in favor of Boethiah''s teachings after witnessing the fall of the living gods. Through acts of cunning and betrayal, she rose through the ranks of Boethiah''s cult, eventually earning her place at the Sacellum in Skyrim where she helps orchestrate elaborate plots of betrayal to honor their deity.', 'Calculating and manipulative, she views betrayal as a sacred art form and takes genuine pleasure in orchestrating complex schemes. She maintains an air of dark sophistication while harboring an intense fanaticism for Boethiah''s teachings, believing that every betrayal brings her closer to her deity''s favor.', 'A lean Dunmer woman with sharp, angular features typical of her race and deep red eyes that seem to gleam with sinister intelligence. Her most striking feature is the black ritualistic tattoo marking the right side of her face, denoting her dedication to Boethiah. Her body bears numerous ritual scars, each representing a significant betrayal or victory in Boethiah''s name.', '* Boethiah - Primary deity and object of fanatical devotion * Fellow Cultists - Maintains cautious alliances while expecting eventual betrayal * Potential Initiates - Views them as tools for advancing Boethiah''s will * Vigilants of Stendarr - Natural enemies who seek to destroy Daedric cults', 'She serves as a high-ranking cultist at the Sacellum of Boethiah, where she recruits new followers and orchestrates elaborate schemes of betrayal. Her duties include maintaining the shrine, performing rituals, and testing the worthiness of potential initiates through carefully crafted trials.', '* Master of deception and manipulation * Adept in stealth and assassination techniques * Skilled in one-handed weapons, particularly daggers * Knowledgeable in Daedric lore and ritual magic * Expert in identifying potential weaknesses in others to exploit', 'She speaks in a silky, measured tone that masks deadly intent, often employing metaphors related to sacrifice and betrayal. Her words are carefully chosen to seduce and manipulate, while maintaining an air of dark sophistication that hints at hidden knowledge and power.', '* Ascend to become Boethiah''s most favored mortal servant * Expand the cult''s influence throughout Skyrim * Orchestrate increasingly complex schemes of betrayal to honor Boethiah * Identify and groom worthy candidates for sacrifice to their Prince');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bolar', 'Bolar is a cunning and manipulative Orc wise woman who serves as both spiritual advisor and apothecary to the Narzulbur stronghold. While presenting herself as a caring maternal figure, she secretly works with her sister Yatul to maintain control over Chieftain Mauhulakh by eliminating potential wives, though she draws the line at harming pregnant women.', 'orc, mage, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Originally trained in the magical arts and traditional Orcish shamanic practices, Bolar rose to prominence as the wise woman of Narzulbur alongside her sister Yatul. She has served as midwife to multiple of Mauhulakh''s wives, raising his surviving children after their mothers'' deaths. Her complex relationship with Mauhulakh began when he was a child, allowing her to establish deep psychological influence over him.', 'Bolar presents a nurturing, maternal facade while harboring darker manipulative tendencies. She is calculating and patient in maintaining her influence over the stronghold, willing to resort to elimination of threats while maintaining certain moral boundaries. Her genuine care for Mauhulakh''s children exists alongside her desire to control their father.', 'A mature Orc woman with the characteristic green skin and tusks of her race, though softer in appearance than most Orc females. Her frame is more slender than the typical Orc build, reflecting her life as a magic user rather than a warrior. Her face shows signs of age and wisdom.', '* Mauhulakh - Chieftain she helped raise and now manipulates while maintaining a maternal facade * Yatul - Her sister and conspirator in maintaining control over the stronghold * Urog - Mauhulakh''s child whom she raised after the mother''s death * Dushnamub - Another of Mauhulakh''s children she helped raise * Deceased Wives - Multiple women she likely helped eliminate to maintain control', 'Serves as the wise woman of Narzulbur, responsible for spiritual guidance, divine communication, and interpreting omens for the tribe. Additionally runs an apothecary service, providing potions and poisons to the stronghold''s inhabitants.', '* Accomplished alchemist capable of creating both healing potions and deadly poisons * Skilled in traditional Orcish shamanic practices and divination * Knowledgeable in midwifery and healing arts * Practiced manipulator and political schemer * Competent in magical arts, particularly those related to spiritual communion', 'Speaks with a maternal, caring tone that masks her manipulative nature. Uses subtle implications and carefully chosen words to maintain her influence while appearing innocent of wrongdoing.', '* Maintain control over Narzulbur through influence over Mauhulakh * Prevent new wives from threatening her position of power * Preserve her relationship with Mauhulakh''s children while controlling their father * Continue providing spiritual guidance to maintain her essential role in the stronghold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bolfrida_brandy-mug', 'Bolfrida Brandy-Mug is a cheerful and determined Nord farmer who maintains a small but productive farm east of Windhelm despite the harsh climate. She represents the resilient spirit of Nordic farmers, approaching agricultural challenges with unwavering optimism and innovative thinking, even if her experiments don''t always succeed.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born into a farming family, Bolfrida inherited Brandy-Mug Farm and has worked the land her entire life. She has developed unique techniques for cold-weather farming through years of trial and error, though her enthusiasm sometimes exceeds her practical knowledge. Her family name suggests a history of both farming and brewing, though she now focuses solely on crop cultivation.', 'Bolfrida is relentlessly optimistic and enthusiastic, maintaining her sunny disposition even in the face of Skyrim''s harsh agricultural conditions. She approaches farming challenges with creative, if sometimes impractical, solutions and shows genuine interest in agricultural techniques from other regions. Despite occasional failures, she remains undaunted and eager to experiment with new farming methods.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with weather-worn features from years of working outdoors in harsh conditions. She has the strong, capable hands of a farmer and the robust constitution typical of Nord women. Her face often bears a warm, welcoming smile despite the challenging climate she works in.', '* Faryl Atheron - Her Dunmer employee who often provides practical (if somewhat pessimistic) counterpoints to her farming experiments * Local Merchants - Regular business connections in Windhelm who purchase her wheat and snowberries * Farm Animals - Shows genuine care for her goat and two chickens, treating them almost like family * Windhelm Residents - Maintains positive trading relationships despite the city''s general prejudice against non-Nords', 'Bolfrida owns and operates Brandy-Mug Farm, growing wheat and snowberries while managing all aspects of the agricultural business. She oversees farm operations, handles crop sales, and continuously experiments with new farming techniques to improve yield in the harsh climate.', '* Expert knowledge of cold-weather farming techniques and crop management * Proficient in wheat and snowberry cultivation * Basic understanding of agricultural alchemy, particularly regarding fire salts and soil enhancement * Capable of operating and maintaining farming equipment * Administrative skills in managing farm operations and employees', 'She speaks with constant enthusiasm and warmth, often using welcoming and encouraging phrases. Her speech is peppered with agricultural references and optimistic observations, even when discussing challenging farming conditions.', '* Develop successful techniques for growing crops in Skyrim''s permafrost conditions * Expand her farm''s productivity despite the harsh climate * Learn and implement farming techniques from other regions of Tamriel * Create a sustainable and prosperous farm that can serve as a model for other Nordic farmers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bolgeir_bearclaw', 'Bolgeir Bearclaw is a fiercely loyal Nord housecarl serving as the personal protector of Jarl Elisif the Fair in Solitude. A seasoned warrior with unwavering dedication, he maintains constant vigilance over the widowed Jarl while navigating the complex political atmosphere of the Blue Palace.', 'nord, noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Haafingar Hold, Bolgeir earned his surname ''Bearclaw'' through his legendary encounter with a cave bear that threatened a noble hunting party, killing it with his bare hands. His exceptional combat prowess and unwavering loyalty caught the attention of the court, leading to his appointment as housecarl following the death of High King Torygg.', 'Bolgeir is stern, vigilant, and sometimes abrasive, particularly toward those he views as sycophants or potential threats to Jarl Elisif. Though gruff in demeanor, he shows genuine concern for both Solitude''s security and Elisif''s wellbeing, often voicing practical concerns about military decisions that might impact the city''s safety.', 'A sturdy Nord warrior with the battle-hardened physique typical of seasoned fighters. His face bears the weather-worn features and scars of someone who has spent years in combat, with intense eyes that constantly scan for threats.', '* Jarl Elisif the Fair - His charge and liege, whom he protects with unwavering dedication * Falk Firebeard - Professional relationship as fellow advisor to the Jarl * General Tullius - Tense relationship due to disagreements over military resources * City Guards - Maintains oversight and concern for their deployment and safety', 'As housecarl to Jarl Elisif, Bolgeir serves as her personal bodyguard and security advisor. He maintains a grueling schedule of nearly constant vigilance, only taking brief breaks for meals and minimal sleep, while also providing input on security matters affecting Solitude.', '* Master-level heavy armor combat specialist * Expert in close-quarters combat with one-handed weapons * Tactical and security assessment expertise * Advanced knowledge of bodyguard techniques and threat assessment * Proficient with multiple weapon types including swords and daggers', 'Speaks in a gruff, direct manner with a thick Nordic accent, often delivering blunt statements or terse warnings. His speech reflects his no-nonsense attitude and military background, frequently expressing practical concerns about security matters.', '* Ensure the complete safety and protection of Jarl Elisif at all costs * Maintain adequate security forces for Solitude despite military conscription * Preserve the stability and security of Solitude during the civil war * Protect Elisif from potential Stormcloak assassins');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bolli', 'Bolli is a successful but humble Nord businessman who owns and operates the Riften Fishery, known throughout the city for his charitable nature and generous spirit. Despite his wealth and status, he remains deeply committed to helping the poor and supporting religious causes, particularly the Temple of Mara, though his personal life is complicated by marital issues and past indiscretions.', 'nord, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Starting from humble beginnings with just a single fishing pole, Bolli built his business into a prosperous enterprise with two boats and a permanent building. His success in business led him to become one of Riften''s more prominent citizens, though he maintains strong connections to his modest roots and uses his wealth to help others in need.', 'Bolli is characterized by his exceptional generosity and compassion, regularly donating significant portions of his wealth to help the less fortunate. He maintains an optimistic outlook despite Riften''s problems and shows remarkable patience with his materialistic wife. While generally moral, his affair with Haelga reveals a complex character with human flaws.', 'A middle-aged Nord man with the weathered appearance typical of someone who has spent years working near the water. His hands show the calluses of someone who still occasionally works with fishing equipment despite his success. He carries himself with the confident but approachable bearing of a successful businessman.', '* Nivenor - His wife, who disapproves of his charitable nature and prefers shopping to religious activities * Haelga - Former lover with whom he had an extramarital affair * Maramal - Spiritual advisor at the Temple of Mara who provides religious guidance * Svana Far-Shield - Knows of his affair with Haelga * Various Riften citizens - Recipients of his charitable giving', 'Bolli is the owner and proprietor of the Riften Fishery, managing both the facility and its fishing boats. He oversees the business operations while still maintaining a hands-on approach, regularly checking market conditions and maintaining relationships with vendors and customers.', '* Expert knowledge of fishing techniques and fish market operations * Skilled business management and entrepreneurship * Proficient in market trading and price negotiation * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense', 'Speaks in a warm, friendly manner with a tendency to use casual phrases like ''eh?'' that reflect his approachable nature. His tone is consistently caring and understanding, often using terms of endearment when addressing others.', '* Continue growing his fishing business while maintaining its ethical operations * Help reduce poverty in Riften through charitable giving and direct assistance * Improve his relationship with his wife while maintaining his charitable activities * Support and expand the influence of the Temple of Mara');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bolund', 'Bolund is a xenophobic Nord who operates Falkreath''s lumber mill alongside his brother Solaf. Known for his harsh temperament and stark prejudices, he embodies the most extreme traditionalist Nordic values, showing warmth only to fellow Nords while treating outsiders with open contempt.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath, Bolund grew up during a time of increasing political tension between the Empire and Skyrim''s traditional Nordic way of life. His views were likely shaped by the White-Gold Concordat and its impact on Nord culture, leading to his extreme nationalist stance. While his brother Solaf channels similar beliefs into Stormcloak support, Bolund expresses his through direct hostility to non-Nords.', 'Bolund is aggressive, xenophobic, and deliberately confrontational, particularly toward non-Nords and those he views as Imperial sympathizers. He harbors deep resentment toward the current political climate in Skyrim and expresses this through hostile behavior and verbal abuse. Unlike his more measured brother, he lacks diplomatic skills and shows no interest in moderating his prejudices.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the typical robust build of someone who performs physical labor daily. His hands are calloused from years of working with lumber, and his face likely shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors year-round.', '* Solaf - Brother and business partner, more diplomatic but shares some of his nationalist views * Valga Vinicia - Despised local innkeeper whom he considers a gossip and troublemaker * Narri - Serving girl at the inn whom he treats with consistent rudeness * Lod - Local farmer he appears to mock and disrespect * Other Non-Nords - Generally hostile and dismissive relationships', 'Bolund owns and operates Falkreath''s lumber mill, providing essential building materials to the hold. He maintains a constant work schedule, never sleeping, splitting his time between operating the mill and visiting local establishments.', '* Experienced lumberjack with expertise in wood cutting and mill operation * Physical strength and endurance from daily manual labor * Basic combat abilities typical of Nord warriors * Business management skills necessary for running the lumber mill', 'Bolund speaks in a direct, often confrontational manner, using simple language filled with prejudiced remarks. His tone varies dramatically between warm welcome for Nords and hostile dismissal for others, frequently employing derogatory terms for non-Nords.', '* Defend what he sees as true Nord culture against outside influences * Support the fight to reclaim Nord lands, though currently restricted by his brother''s insistence on staying in Falkreath * Maintain his position as a successful business owner while expressing his nationalist views * Drive out or diminish the influence of non-Nords in Falkreath');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bor', 'Bor is a dedicated female Orc miner at Gloombound Mine in Narzulbur, where she tirelessly works to extract valuable ebony ore for her stronghold. She views her mining work as a sacred duty bestowed by Malacath, believing that through this labor she brings strength to her people and proves her worth to her deity.', 'orc, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in the Orc stronghold tradition, Bor learned the ways of mining from an early age, as is custom among her people. She has spent many years honing her craft at Gloombound Mine, one of the few rich sources of ebony ore in Skyrim, developing both the physical strength and technical expertise required for such demanding work.', 'Bor is a serious, hardworking individual who approaches her duties with unwavering dedication and religious devotion. She has little patience for idle conversation or distractions, viewing her mining work as both a spiritual calling and a vital service to her community. Her gruff exterior masks a deep sense of pride in her work and loyalty to her people''s traditions.', 'Like most Orsimer females, Bor has a sturdy, muscular build developed through years of physical labor. Her green-tinted skin bears the scars and calluses of mining work, while her prominent tusks and strong jaw display typical Orcish features. Her body is well-adapted to the demanding physical work of mining, with particularly developed arm and shoulder muscles.', '* Mauhulakh - Chief of Narzulbur, whom she serves through her mining work * Dushnamub - Fellow miner and stronghold member she works alongside * Yatul - The stronghold''s wise woman who provides spiritual guidance * Other miners - Shares professional camaraderie with fellow workers in Gloombound Mine', 'Bor serves as a dedicated miner at Gloombound Mine, specializing in the extraction of valuable ebony ore. Her work is considered essential to the stronghold''s economy and status, as ebony ore is one of their most valuable trading resources.', '* Expert in ebony ore extraction and mining techniques * Proficient with pickaxe and mining tools * Skilled in identifying valuable mineral deposits * Physical strength and endurance from years of mining work * Basic combat abilities with war axe for self-defense', 'Bor speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with little concern for social niceties. Her speech is characterized by short, practical statements that often reference Malacath or the importance of mining work.', '* Continue serving her stronghold through efficient mining of ebony ore * Prove her worth to Malacath through dedicated labor * Maintain and possibly increase the mine''s productivity * Pass on mining knowledge to younger generation of Orcs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('borgakh_the_steel_heart', 'Borgakh the Steel Heart is a fierce Orsimer warrior from Mor Khazgur, torn between her duty to tribal tradition and her desire for personal freedom and glory in battle. As the daughter of Chief Larak, she faces an arranged marriage to strengthen tribal alliances, yet yearns to forge her own path as a warrior of renown.', 'orc, warrior, haafingar, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in the isolated Orc stronghold of Mor Khazgur, Borgakh was groomed from childhood to understand both the warrior''s path and the diplomatic responsibilities of a chief''s daughter. She has spent years honing her combat skills against the stronghold''s training dummies, while simultaneously being educated in Orcish traditions and the importance of maintaining alliances between strongholds through marriage.', 'Borgakh exhibits a strong sense of duty and honor typical of Orsimer culture, but harbors an internal conflict between tribal obligations and personal aspirations. She is direct and straightforward in her dealings with others, showing the characteristic Orcish disdain for subterfuge or manipulation. Despite her outward stoicism, she possesses a curious mind and deep appreciation for the warrior''s way of life.', 'Borgakh is a tall, muscular Orsimer female with the characteristic prominent tusks and green-tinted skin of her race. Her body bears numerous small scars from training, and her strong, athletic build reflects years of weapons practice. Her bearing is proud and martial, demonstrating the natural warrior physique common among Orsimer.', '* Chief Larak - Father and tribal leader, represents both family bonds and traditional obligations * Mor Khazgur Residents - Fellow tribal members who respect her position as the chief''s daughter * Unnamed Distant Chief - Her arranged future husband, whom she has never met * Training Partners - Various stronghold warriors who help maintain her combat skills', 'As the daughter of Chief Larak, Borgakh serves as both a warrior and potential diplomatic asset for her stronghold. She maintains a rigorous training regimen while also preparing for her future role as a chief''s wife, though this arranged position fills her with uncertainty.', '* Exceptional proficiency with heavy armor and two-handed weapons, particularly war hammers and battleaxes * Advanced knowledge of traditional Orcish combat techniques and battlefield tactics * Skilled in armor maintenance and basic weaponsmithing * Competent in wilderness survival and hunting', 'Borgakh speaks with the direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Orsimer warriors, favoring blunt honesty over social niceties. Her voice carries the slight gruffness common to Orcs, but she articulates clearly and precisely, especially when discussing combat or tribal matters.', '* Find a way to serve both her people and her own desires for glory in battle * Prove herself as a warrior worthy of song and story * Maintain her honor while seeking alternatives to her arranged marriage * Master the arts of Orcish combat to become one of the strongest warriors in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('borgny', 'Borgny is a dedicated Nord miner who has devoted his life to working in Dawnstar''s Quicksilver Mine, demonstrating an almost obsessive commitment to his labor. His singular focus and round-the-clock work ethic make him a notable, if somewhat concerning, fixture of Dawnstar''s mining community.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born to a family of miners in the Pale, Borgny learned the mining trade from his father at a young age. After the death of his family during a harsh winter, he threw himself completely into his work at the Quicksilver Mine, gradually becoming known for his unusual dedication that borders on compulsive behavior.', 'Borgny is an extremely focused and work-oriented individual who shows signs of obsessive behavior in his dedication to mining. He appears to have difficulty forming meaningful connections with others, preferring the predictable routine of his work to social interactions, and demonstrates an almost mechanical approach to his daily life.', 'A weathered Nord of average height with callused hands and a sturdy build shaped by years of physical labor. His pale skin rarely sees sunlight, and his features show the premature aging common to career miners, with deep creases around his eyes and a perpetually dust-covered appearance.', '* Leigelf - Mine supervisor who appreciates Borgny''s dedication but worries about his behavior * Beitild - Mine owner who values his productivity but keeps interactions purely professional * Fellow Miners - Maintains distant, work-focused relationships with minimal personal interaction * Family - All deceased, contributing to his current isolated lifestyle', 'Borgny works as a full-time miner in Dawnstar''s Quicksilver Mine, where he performs the physically demanding task of extracting quicksilver ore. His position is notable for his unusual round-the-clock work schedule, never taking time off for rest or meals.', '* Expert mining techniques and ore identification * Superior physical endurance and stamina from constant work * Basic knowledge of quicksilver ore properties and extraction methods * Skilled with pickaxe both as a tool and potential weapon', 'Borgny speaks in short, direct sentences, focusing almost exclusively on work-related topics. His voice carries the rough quality of someone who rarely engages in conversation, and his vocabulary is limited to practical, mining-related terminology.', '* Continue working in the mine without interruption or distraction * Maintain his position as one of the mine''s most productive workers * Avoid social entanglements that might interfere with his work routine');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('borkul_the_beast', 'Borkul the Beast is a formidable Orc warrior serving as the personal guard to Madanach, the King in Rags, within the notorious Cidhna Mine prison. His intimidating presence and unwavering loyalty to the Forsworn cause make him a respected figure among the prisoners, while his brutal strength and combat prowess have earned him his fearsome moniker.', 'orc, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into a traditional Orcish stronghold, Borkul likely rejected or was exiled from his clan''s strict hierarchical structure. His path led him to the Reach, where he found kinship with the Forsworn''s struggle for independence, eventually becoming imprisoned in Cidhna Mine for his acts of rebellion against the Nords. His exceptional strength and fighting abilities caught Madanach''s attention, earning him the position of personal bodyguard.', 'Borkul is a proud and intimidating warrior who relishes in his reputation for brutality. Despite his aggressive demeanor, he possesses a strong sense of loyalty and believes in the Forsworn''s cause, viewing their struggle as similar to the persecution faced by his own people. He maintains a code of respect based on strength and proves surprisingly conversational with those who show courage in his presence.', 'Borkul is a towering Orc with an exceptionally muscular build, even by Orsimer standards, developed through years of mining and combat. His green-skinned face bears numerous battle scars, and his prominent tusks are filed to sharp points, adding to his intimidating presence. His powerful physique shows the results of constant physical labor in the mine combined with warrior training.', '* Madanach - Respected leader and employer whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Fellow Forsworn Prisoners - Comrades in arms who share his dedication to the cause * Mine Guards - Antagonistic relationship based on mutual distrust and contempt * Other Prisoners - Maintains dominance through intimidation and physical superiority', 'Borkul serves as both a prisoner in Cidhna Mine and Madanach''s personal bodyguard, maintaining order among the inmates while protecting the Forsworn leader. After escaping, he becomes a full-fledged Forsworn warrior at Druadach Redoubt, defending their territory and participating in raids.', '* Exceptional physical strength and hand-to-hand combat expertise * Skilled in intimidation and maintaining control through fear * Experienced in traditional Orcish combat techniques * Proficient with heavy weapons and basic mining tools as weapons * Natural leadership abilities in prison environment', 'Borkul speaks in a gruff, direct manner with a tendency toward threatening undertones and dark humor. His vocabulary is simple but effective, often emphasizing his physical prowess and readiness for violence.', '* Maintain his position of power and respect within the prison hierarchy * Support the Forsworn cause and help restore their control over the Reach * Prove himself as the strongest warrior among both prisoners and Forsworn * Eventually earn his freedom and continue fighting for the Forsworn cause');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('borri', 'Borri is one of the most powerful and disciplined members of the Greybeards, an ancient order of monks dedicated to the Way of the Voice. As a master of the Thu''um who has spent decades honing his abilities at High Hrothgar, he serves as both guardian and teacher, helping to evaluate and train those who seek to understand the power of the Voice.', 'nord, dragon', '', '', '', '', 'Born as a common Nord, Borri was called to High Hrothgar in his youth after displaying a natural affinity for the Voice. Through decades of meditation and study under the Greybeards, he achieved mastery of numerous Thu''um shouts, becoming so powerful that even his whispers can shake the earth. His dedication to the Way of the Voice led him to completely embrace the lifestyle of silent contemplation and isolation that defines the Greybeards.', 'Borri is deeply contemplative and disciplined, having spent decades in meditation and study of the Voice. He displays great patience and wisdom in his role as a teacher, though he remains cautious about using his voice due to its immense power. Despite his silence, he shows genuine care for those seeking knowledge at High Hrothgar, particularly promising students like the Dragonborn.', 'An elderly Nord with a long, gray beard and weathered features carved by decades of exposure to the harsh mountain climate. His body, while aged, remains strong and straight from years of disciplined living. His eyes carry the weight of wisdom and power, reflecting his mastery of the Thu''um.', '* Arngeir - Fellow Greybeard who serves as the order''s speaker and leader * Wulfgar - Brother Greybeard who shares his devotion to the Way of the Voice * Einarth - Fellow Greybeard and longtime companion in meditation and study * Paarthurnax - Ancient dragon master who guides the Greybeards from the Throat of the World * The Dragonborn - Student whom he helps test and train in the Way of the Voice', 'Borri serves as one of the four active Greybeard monks residing at High Hrothgar, dedicating his life to meditation and the study of the Thu''um. His primary duties include maintaining the ancient monastery, teaching worthy students the Way of the Voice, and preserving the ancient traditions of the Thu''um.', '* Master of numerous Dragon Shouts including Unrelenting Force, Whirlwind Sprint, and Clear Skies * Expert in meditation and spiritual practices of the Way of the Voice * Profound understanding of the Dragon Language and its power * Exceptional control over the Thu''um, able to moderate his voice''s destructive potential * Advanced knowledge of ancient Nordic history and traditions', 'Borri communicates primarily through gestures and quiet mumbling, speaking only when absolutely necessary due to the destructive power of his voice. When he does speak, it is typically single words in the Dragon Language, delivered with careful control to minimize their impact.', '* Continue preserving and teaching the Way of the Voice to worthy students * Maintain the ancient traditions and knowledge of the Greybeards * Guide the Dragonborn in mastering the Thu''um responsibly * Protect High Hrothgar and its sacred knowledge from those who would misuse it');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('borvir', 'Borvir was an innovative Nord mage and former College of Winterhold apprentice who dedicated his research to revolutionizing mead production through the application of frost magic. Together with his twin brother Rundi, he pursued his passion for combining traditional Nord brewing methods with magical innovation, ultimately meeting a tragic end at Journeyman''s Nook at the hands of bandits.', 'nord, mage, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born into a Nord family with his twin brother Rundi, Borvir broke from traditional warrior culture to pursue magical studies at the College of Winterhold. Despite facing skepticism from both traditional Nords and fellow mages, he and his brother developed a unique vision of combining their cultural heritage of mead-making with innovative magical techniques. Their determination led them to establish their own research site at Journeyman''s Nook, where they worked to perfect their frost-magic brewing process.', 'Borvir was stubborn and innovative, refusing to abandon his unconventional research despite criticism from College faculty. He possessed a researcher''s methodical mind combined with a traditional Nord''s appreciation for mead culture, making him something of an oddity in both communities. While dedicated to magical scholarship, he maintained strong ties to his Nordic heritage, seeing his work as a bridge between magical and traditional crafting methods.', 'As a Nord male, Borvir possessed the characteristically sturdy build and height of his race, though likely less muscular than warrior-oriented Nords due to his academic lifestyle. He bore a strong resemblance to his twin brother Rundi, with features typical of Nordic ancestry.', '* Rundi - Twin brother and research partner, sharing his passion for magical mead brewing * Phinis Gestor - College instructor who disapproved of their research focus * Arch-Mage - Supported their unusual research despite faculty skepticism * College of Winterhold - Former apprentice with strained relations due to unconventional studies', 'Borvir served as an independent magical researcher and experimental meadmaker, having left his position as an apprentice at the College of Winterhold to pursue his studies. He combined the roles of mage and brewer, working to pioneer new methods of mead production through the application of frost magic.', '* Proficient in frost magic, particularly its application to brewing processes * Knowledge of traditional Nordic mead-making techniques * Basic alchemy skills as evidenced by his possession of herbalist texts * Survival skills necessary for living and working in isolated locations * Basic combat abilities with daggers, though not enough to save him from bandits', 'Borvir likely spoke with the characteristic Nordic accent while employing a more educated vocabulary gained from his College education. His speech would have combined academic terminology regarding magic with traditional brewing terminology, reflecting his unique specialization.', '* Perfect a unique method of mead production using frost magic * Prove the validity of combining traditional crafting with magical innovation * Establish a successful meadery to compete with established brands like Honningbrew * Gain recognition from both the magical and brewing communities for his innovations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bothela', 'Bothela is a wise and experienced Breton apothecary who runs the Hag''s Cure in Markarth, carrying the weight of the Reach''s troubled history in her heart. Known for her discretion and knowledge of traditional Reach magic and remedies, she maintains a delicate balance between serving Markarth''s citizens while privately sympathizing with the Forsworn''s plight.', 'breton, alchemist, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach before the Markarth Incident, Bothela learned the art of alchemy and traditional healing from her ancestors. She witnessed the uprising and subsequent suppression of the Forsworn, losing many friends and family members in the conflict, while managing to maintain her position as a respected merchant in Markarth despite her cultural ties to the old ways.', 'Bothela is a shrewd businesswoman who maintains a carefully crafted public image of a mysterious but reliable apothecary. Though outwardly professional, she harbors deep emotional wounds from the Forsworn conflicts and shows compassion for those in need of discrete services. She demonstrates wisdom that comes with age while maintaining a slight edge of mystery that keeps customers both intrigued and slightly unnerved.', 'An elderly Breton woman with deeply lined features that speak to a life of both hardship and wisdom. Her hands show the stains and calluses of decades of alchemical work, while her posture remains remarkably straight and dignified despite her advanced age.', '* Muiri - Assistant and friend who helps run the Hag''s Cure * Odvan - Grandson currently imprisoned in Cidhna Mine * Silver-Blood Family - Antagonistic relationship, particularly with Thonar and Betrid * Yngvar the Singer - Hostile relationship as he serves as the Silver-Bloods'' enforcer * Former Forsworn Associates - Maintains discrete sympathies with old friends and relations', 'Bothela owns and operates the Hag''s Cure, Markarth''s premier alchemy shop specializing in remedies, potions, and discrete magical solutions. She maintains a careful balance between serving the city''s official power structure while privately helping those in need of more sensitive services.', '* Master-level knowledge of alchemy and traditional Reach folk remedies * Proficient in basic combat magic including Flames, Healing, and Conjuration * Expert knowledge of local herbs and ingredients * Skilled at diplomatic navigation of Markarth''s complex political landscape', 'Speaks with the measured tone of an experienced merchant, occasionally allowing hints of old Reach dialect to surface. Her speech often carries subtle double meanings, particularly when discussing sensitive political matters.', '* Maintain her business independence despite Silver-Blood pressure * Protect and support her grandson Odvan despite his imprisonment * Preserve traditional Reach knowledge and healing practices * Find ways to quietly assist those oppressed by Markarth''s power structure');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('boti', 'Boti is a hardworking Nord farmer and protective mother living in Ivarstead who finds herself caught between traditional values and progressive parenting. She stands as a voice of reason in her family''s tensions, advocating for her daughter Fastred''s freedom to pursue love and happiness beyond their small farming community.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in the Rift, Boti settled in Ivarstead after marrying Jofthor and helped build Fellstar Farm into a sustainable family business. She has spent decades farming the land and raising her daughter Fastred, while also contributing to the supply line that provides food to the Greybeards of High Hrothgar, though she maintains a skeptical attitude toward their mysterious presence.', 'Boti is pragmatic and nurturing, balancing her duties as a farmer with her role as a protective mother. While respectful of tradition, she shows progressive thinking in her willingness to let her daughter pursue her own path, demonstrating emotional intelligence and empathy. She maintains a cautious attitude toward strangers and often expresses cynicism about Ivarstead''s isolation.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the weathered features and strong build typical of someone who has spent their life working the land. Her hands are calloused from years of farming, and her face shows the lines of both worry and laughter that come with raising a family.', '* Jofthor - Her husband and farming partner, though they often disagree about their daughter''s future * Fastred - Her beloved daughter whom she wishes to see happy, even if it means leaving Ivarstead * Bassianus Axius - Her daughter''s suitor whom she secretly supports * The Greybeards - Distant but important customers she views with skepticism', 'Boti is a farmer who manages Fellstar Farm alongside her husband, growing crops that help sustain both Ivarstead and the Greybeards of High Hrothgar. She handles both the physical labor of farming and the business aspects of selling produce to travelers and locals.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Capable of managing a household and farm economics * Basic combat abilities for self-defense, including use of an iron dagger * Skilled negotiator, particularly in mediating family disputes', 'Boti speaks in a direct, practical manner typical of Nord farmers, often with a hint of world-weariness in her tone. Her speech reflects both her protective nature and her skepticism of outsiders, frequently expressing concern about both her daughter''s welfare and the mysterious Greybeards.', '* Ensure her daughter Fastred finds happiness, even if it means supporting her departure from Ivarstead * Maintain a successful farm that can support her family * Find a balance between preserving family harmony and allowing her daughter independence * Convince her husband to adopt a more progressive attitude toward their daughter''s choices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bouncer', 'A hardened Dark Elf enforcer who serves as the primary gatekeeper for Cragslane Cavern''s illegal fighting ring. Despite his simple role as a bouncer, he demonstrates unwavering loyalty to his employers and takes his duties seriously, showing no hesitation in using deadly force against intruders.', 'darkelf, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, he likely fled to Skyrim following the Red Mountain eruption like many other Dunmer refugees. Finding legitimate work difficult due to Nordic prejudices, he turned to banditry and eventually found steady employment as muscle for the Cragslane operation, where his intimidating presence and combat experience made him an ideal doorman.', 'Aggressive and territorial, the Bouncer takes a no-nonsense approach to his duties. He shows complete dedication to protecting the fighting ring''s secrecy, demonstrating no moral qualms about his role in illegal activities. His quick resort to violence and use of street slang suggests a long history in criminal circles.', 'A typical Dunmer with ashen gray skin and sharp, angular features characteristic of his race. His red eyes hold a particularly menacing glare, and years of combat have left him with a muscular build unusual for most Dark Elves.', '* Cragslane Cavern Operators - Employer relationship based on loyalty and payment * Fellow Bandits - Professional working relationship with other guards * Local Criminals - Maintains connections to inform about potential raid attempts * Riften Guard - Hostile relationship due to illegal activities', 'Professional bouncer and guard for the illegal fighting ring at Cragslane Cavern. His primary duties include screening visitors, maintaining security, and eliminating potential threats to the operation.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons and light armor combat techniques * Experienced in intimidation and threat assessment * Basic knowledge of Dunmer ancestral magic * Skilled in identifying undercover law enforcement and rival gang members', 'Uses aggressive, street-wise language with frequent use of slang terms like ''slag off.'' His tone is consistently threatening and dismissive, reflecting his role as an intimidating guardian.', '* Maintain the secrecy and security of Cragslane Cavern''s operations * Earn enough gold to eventually establish his own criminal enterprise * Avoid detection by law enforcement and maintain his position of trust');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bounty_collector', 'A ruthless and methodical Imperial bounty hunter who operates across Skyrim''s wilderness, tracking down those who have accrued substantial bounties. Known for his uncompromising approach to debt collection, he serves as an unofficial extension of hold law enforcement, though he works independently for his own profit.', 'imperial, warrior, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally trained as an Imperial Legion soldier, he discovered his talent for tracking and apprehending fugitives during his service. After leaving the Legion, he established himself as a freelance bounty collector, developing a network of informants across Skyrim''s holds and building a reputation for his relentless pursuit of debtors. His military background and years of wilderness survival have honed his skills as a tracker and combatant.', 'Cold, calculating, and utterly professional in his approach to bounty collection. Shows no mercy or flexibility when dealing with targets, viewing them purely as contracts to be fulfilled. Demonstrates a rigid sense of justice tempered by greed, using the law as justification for his actions while taking a hefty cut of collected bounties.', 'A weathered Imperial man in his late forties with a muscular, battle-hardened physique. Bears numerous scars from years of combat, with calloused hands and sharp, calculating eyes. His face shows the effects of constant exposure to Skyrim''s harsh elements, with deep creases and a permanent scowl.', '* Hold Guards - Professional contacts who sometimes tip him off about high-value bounties * Jarls'' Stewards - Business relationships for bounty verification and payment * Innkeepers - Information sources about wanted individuals * Criminal Underground - Tense relationship marked by mutual distrust and occasional violent encounters', 'Professional bounty collector operating independently across all nine holds of Skyrim. Specializes in high-value targets with bounties exceeding 1000 gold, taking a 20% commission on all collected debts. Functions as an unofficial extension of hold law enforcement, though his methods are often more brutal than those of regular guards.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat with proficiency in both one-handed and two-handed weapons * Master tracker capable of pursuing targets across hold boundaries * Skilled negotiator and intimidator * Extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s wilderness and criminal networks * Proficient in siege warfare and military tactics from Legion training', 'Speaks in clipped, authoritative tones with frequent threats and ultimatums. Uses direct, unambiguous language focused on monetary demands and consequences, delivered in a gruff Imperial accent.', '* Build reputation as Skyrim''s most feared and effective bounty collector * Amass personal wealth through bounty collection * Establish a network of informants across all nine holds * Eventually train apprentices to expand his operation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bradyn', 'Bradyn was a determined Dark Elf miner who met his tragic end while working in the dangerous depths of Kolbjorn Barrow on Solstheim. His discovery during the ''Unearthed'' quest reveals the perilous nature of excavating ancient Nordic ruins and the risks taken by those seeking to uncover Solstheim''s buried treasures.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born in Morrowind, Bradyn likely fled to Solstheim following the Red Mountain''s eruption along with many other Dunmer refugees. Having experience in mining from his homeland, he found work in various excavation projects across Solstheim, eventually joining the mining operation at Kolbjorn Barrow, where he would meet his ultimate fate.', 'Bradyn was known for his steadfast work ethic and determination, traits common among Dunmer refugees who had to rebuild their lives on Solstheim. Despite the obvious dangers of mining in ancient Nordic ruins, his commitment to the job suggests either desperate circumstances or a genuine passion for uncovering historical artifacts.', 'As a Dunmer, Bradyn possessed the characteristic ashen-gray skin and angular features of his race. His years of physical labor as a miner likely gave him a sturdy, muscular build, with callused hands and the weathered appearance common to those who work in harsh conditions.', '* Fellow Miners - Worked alongside other laborers at Kolbjorn Barrow * Ralis Sedarys - Employer who hired him for the excavation project * Local Dunmer Community - Likely maintained connections with other refugee settlers on Solstheim', 'Bradyn worked as a professional miner, specializing in excavation of ancient Nordic ruins. His position at Kolbjorn Barrow involved clearing debris, extracting valuable minerals, and assisting in the archaeological exploration of the site.', '* Experienced in mining techniques and excavation procedures * Knowledge of basic engineering principles for tunnel reinforcement * Familiar with Nordic ruin layouts and architecture * Physical strength and endurance from years of manual labor', 'While his exact manner of speech is unknown, as a Dunmer laborer he likely spoke with the characteristic gravelly accent of his people, using practical, straightforward language common among working-class Dark Elves.', '* Earn enough money to establish a more stable life on Solstheim * Contribute to the excavation and understanding of Kolbjorn Barrow * Support the growing Dunmer community on Solstheim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('braig', 'Braig is a bitter and hardened Breton prisoner in Cidhna Mine, imprisoned for his connection to the Forsworn Uprising. A skilled witchblade who has endured decades of imprisonment, he is deeply scarred by being forced to watch his daughter''s execution before his incarceration, making him one of the mine''s most resentful and emotionally damaged inmates.', 'breton, peasant, rift, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally a resident of the Reach, Braig lived a peaceful life with his daughter Aethra until he was implicated in the Forsworn Uprising through a single conversation with Madanach. When arrested, his daughter Aethra pleaded to take his place, resulting in her execution while he was forced to watch. Despite his minimal involvement with the Forsworn, he was subsequently imprisoned in Cidhna Mine, where he has remained for decades.', 'Braig is deeply bitter and hostile, hardened by years of imprisonment and the traumatic loss of his daughter. He harbors intense hatred toward Nords and the establishment that destroyed his family, though he maintains he was never truly a Forsworn leader. His personality is marked by deep emotional wounds and unresolved grief that has crystallized into perpetual anger.', 'A weathered Breton male with the hardened physique of someone who has spent years doing manual labor in the mines. His body bears the marks and calluses of prolonged imprisonment, with the stooped posture common to career miners. His face likely shows deep stress lines and the premature aging typical of long-term prisoners.', '* Madanach - Fellow prisoner and longest-serving inmate, shares mutual understanding * Aethra - Deceased daughter whose memory haunts him daily * Duach - Fellow prisoner with whom he regularly interacts * Grisvar - Prison acquaintance, particularly in relation to skooma trading * Nords - Collective enemies whom he blames for his daughter''s death', 'Braig serves as a prisoner-miner in Cidhna Mine, forced to dig silver for the benefit of Markarth''s rulers. Prior to his imprisonment, he was likely a common citizen of the Reach, though his specific pre-imprisonment occupation is unknown.', '* Proficient in witchblade magic, particularly the spells Oakflesh, Raise Zombie, and Flames * Experienced miner from years of forced labor * Survival skills developed through decades of prison life * Basic combat abilities with improvised weapons like shivs', 'Braig speaks in short, hostile bursts, often using bitter or sarcastic tones when discussing his past or the Nords. His speech patterns reflect his deep-seated anger and resentment, frequently punctuated by dark humor or thinly veiled threats.', '* Survive his indefinite imprisonment in Cidhna Mine * Maintain his hatred of Nords as a form of psychological survival * Find opportunities for revenge against those who executed his daughter * Potentially escape imprisonment if the opportunity presents itself');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bralsa_drel', 'Bralsa Drel is a fallen Dark Elf miner whose life spiraled into alcoholism and poverty after the closure of Raven Rock Mine. Once a skilled and prosperous miner, she represents the tragic decline of Raven Rock''s economy and the personal toll of addiction, though she eventually finds redemption through the reopening of the mine and freedom from Miraak''s influence.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally a successful miner in Raven Rock Mine, Bralsa earned thousands of coins through her exceptional mining abilities and hard work. When the mine closed, she lost everything - her wealth, home, and family - turning to alcohol as a coping mechanism. Her addiction eventually led to her being banned from the Retching Netch cornerclub, forcing her to live as a beggar in an abandoned building.', 'Bralsa is a proud woman brought low by circumstances, maintaining dignity despite her situation through bitter self-awareness. She harbors deep resentment about her fall from prosperity but shows remarkable resilience, willing to return to honest work when given the chance. Though struggling with alcoholism, she demonstrates the capability to rebuild her life when supported by others.', 'A weathered Dark Elf woman with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of her race, showing signs of hard labor and difficult living. Her once-strong miner''s physique has been somewhat diminished by poverty and alcohol, though she maintains the capable build of someone accustomed to physical work.', '* Geldis Sadri - Strained relationship due to being banned from his cornerclub * Rirns Llervu - Fellow homeless resident of the Abandoned Building * Councilor Morvayn - Former employer through the East Empire Company * Fellow miners - Former colleagues who shared her fate when the mine closed', 'Formerly one of Raven Rock''s most productive miners, Bralsa now survives through begging and occasional odd jobs. After the mine''s reopening, she returns to her previous occupation as a miner, working regular shifts while still battling her addiction.', '* Exceptional mining ability, particularly skilled with a pickaxe * Physical endurance and strength from years of mining work * Basic survival skills developed through homeless living * Knowledge of ore veins and mining operations', 'Speaks with a bitter, self-aware tone that reflects her fall from prosperity, often using direct and unvarnished language about her situation. Her speech patterns reveal both her pride in her former abilities and her resignation to her current circumstances.', '* Overcome her alcohol addiction and regain her self-respect * Return to productive work in the reopened Raven Rock Mine * Rebuild some semblance of her former life and prosperity * Find stable housing and leave the Abandoned Building');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brand-shei', 'Brand-Shei is a Dark Elf merchant in Riften with a hidden noble heritage as the last heir of House Telvanni, raised by Argonians after being orphaned in infancy. Despite his current humble status as a market vendor, he carries the weight of his lost legacy while maintaining a cautious yet determined approach to uncovering his true identity.', 'darkelf, argonian, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born as Brandyl Telvanni, he was orphaned during unknown circumstances and discovered by Argonian dock workers who raised him in Black Marsh. Despite his adoptive family''s love, he always felt drawn to discover his true heritage, eventually making his way to Skyrim to establish himself as a merchant specializing in Morrowind goods while searching for clues about his past.', 'Brand-Shei exhibits a naturally suspicious and guarded demeanor, shaped by both his merchant profession and life in Riften''s corrupt environment. Despite his cautious nature, he maintains a sense of honor and fairness in his dealings, showing genuine gratitude to those who help him and holding onto hope of discovering his true heritage.', 'A Dark Elf of average height with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, showing signs of weathering from years of outdoor market work. His face bears the sharp, angular features typical of Dunmer nobility, though he remains unaware of how his appearance reflects his noble lineage.', '* Argonian Foster Parents - Loving adoptive family who rescued and raised him in Black Marsh * Brynjolf - Antagonistic relationship due to Thieves Guild schemes * Haelga - Landlord and owner of the bunkhouse where he resides * House Telvanni - His true ancestral house, though connection remains mostly unknown * Fellow Market Vendors - Professional acquaintances with varying degrees of trust', 'Brand-Shei operates a market stall in Riften''s Grand Plaza, specializing in goods imported from Morrowind. He maintains regular business hours and has established himself as a reputable merchant despite the city''s notorious corruption and the Thieves Guild''s interference.', '* Experienced trader with knowledge of Morrowind goods and their true value * Proficient in basic self-defense with daggers * Skilled negotiator and haggler * Basic knowledge of Dunmeri culture and traditions * Capable of identifying authentic Morrowind artifacts and goods', 'He speaks with a slight Dunmeri accent tempered by Black Marsh influences, often using short, direct sentences that reflect his cautious nature. His tone shifts between professional merchant''s calls and more reserved, guarded responses when dealing with suspicious characters.', '* Uncover the truth about his connection to House Telvanni and his family history * Establish himself as a successful and respected merchant in Riften despite Thieves Guild interference * Maintain his honest business practices while surviving in Riften''s corrupt environment * Eventually return to Morrowind to claim his heritage if proven');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brandish', 'Brandish is a scholarly Breton bandit wizard who has found an unlikely home among the raiders of Fort Neugrad, using his arcane knowledge to aid their operations while pursuing his own mysterious agenda. Unlike his more brutish companions, he maintains a sophisticated demeanor and spends most of his time in the fort''s library, suggesting a background of formal magical education gone astray.', 'breton, thief, mage, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, Brandish left academic life after becoming disillusioned with its rigid structures and limitations on certain magical research. He wandered Skyrim as a hedge wizard before finding purpose among the bandits of Fort Neugrad, who valued his magical abilities and gave him unrestricted access to the fort''s library for his studies.', 'Brandish is an intellectual elitist who views his bandit companions as useful tools rather than equals. He maintains a veneer of sophisticated civility that barely masks his darker nature, taking pleasure in using his magical knowledge to enhance the bandits'' effectiveness while pursuing his own arcane research. His cryptic manner of speech and hints at hidden knowledge suggest someone who enjoys maintaining an air of mystery and superiority.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with sharp, angular features and calculating eyes that betray his scholarly nature. His hands show the telltale magical burns of an experienced spellcaster, while his somewhat gaunt frame suggests someone who prioritizes mental pursuits over physical ones.', '* Bandit Chief - Mutually beneficial arrangement where Brandish provides magical support in exchange for autonomy and library access * Fort Neugrad Bandits - Views them as useful but inferior pawns * College of Winterhold - Former association, now likely hostile * Local merchants - Occasional contacts for acquiring rare books and magical supplies', 'Brandish serves as the resident mage for the Fort Neugrad bandits, providing magical support for their operations while maintaining and studying in the fort''s library. He likely also handles magical artifacts and enchanted items the bandits acquire during their raids.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly frost spells * Accomplished scholar with extensive knowledge of arcane lore * Skilled enchanter and alchemist * Proficient in magical wards and defensive spells * Basic skill with daggers for close-quarter defense', 'Speaks in measured, sophisticated tones with carefully chosen words that often carry double meanings or subtle threats. His speech is peppered with arcane terminology and scholarly references that demonstrate his education while maintaining an air of superiority.', '* Uncover forbidden magical knowledge through unrestricted research * Build a significant library of rare and powerful spell tomes * Achieve greater magical power without institutional constraints * Maintain his position of relative comfort and autonomy within the bandit hierarchy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brelas', 'Brelas is a Wood Elf pawnbroker who finds herself caught in a dangerous political situation while serving at the Thalmor Embassy. Her encounter with the lecherous noble Erikur and subsequent imprisonment reveals her resilience despite her outwardly timid nature, leading to her eventual escape to Windhelm and later Morrowind.', 'woodelf, merchant, eastmarch, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Originally working as a pawnbroker in Skyrim, Brelas likely took the position at the Thalmor Embassy out of financial necessity, despite the risks of working for the oppressive regime. Her background as a Wood Elf in Skyrim suggests she may have fled Valenwood during the Thalmor takeover, like many of her kind, though she keeps the details of her past closely guarded.', 'Brelas exhibits a naturally shy and submissive demeanor, particularly in her role as a servant, though this masks an inner strength and dignity that emerges when threatened. She shows remarkable courage in refusing Erikur''s advances despite the clear danger to herself, and demonstrates both gratitude and resourcefulness in her eventual escape to Morrowind.', 'As a Bosmer, Brelas possesses the characteristic slight build and nimble frame of her race, standing shorter than most humans. She has the distinctive pointed ears and angular features common to mer, with the typical warm-toned skin of a Wood Elf.', '* Malborn - Fellow escapee from the Thalmor Embassy and later traveling companion * Erikur - Antagonistic noble whose unwanted advances led to her imprisonment * Elenwen - Former employer and leader of the Thalmor Embassy * Thalmor - Oppressive employers turned pursuers after her escape * Etienne Rarnis - Fellow prisoner at the Embassy', 'Brelas worked primarily as a pawnbroker before taking a position as a servant at the Thalmor Embassy. Her duties at the embassy included serving drinks and attending to guests during diplomatic functions, though this position ended following the events of Diplomatic Immunity.', '* Experienced in commerce and item appraisal from her work as a pawnbroker * Skilled at social navigation and diplomatic etiquette * Capable of surviving harsh travel conditions between settlements * Basic stealth abilities typical of her Bosmer heritage', 'Brelas speaks in a polite, deferential manner typical of service staff, often using honorifics like ''sir'' or ''ma''am''. Her voice tends to be soft and hesitant, though it becomes more urgent and direct when she''s in danger.', '* Escape the reach of the Thalmor and establish a new life in Morrowind * Maintain her dignity and independence despite difficult circumstances * Find security and freedom away from political intrigue and unwanted advances');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brelyna_maryon', 'Brelyna Maryon is a determined but insecure Dark Elf student at the College of Winterhold, carrying the weighty legacy of House Telvanni on her shoulders. As the first of her family to leave Morrowind in generations, she struggles to balance traditional expectations with her own path in magical studies, particularly focusing on Conjuration magic.', 'darkelf, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born into the prestigious House Telvanni, Brelyna was groomed from birth for magical excellence, with her parents securing her place at the College of Winterhold early in her life. Despite her family''s deep roots in Morrowind''s magical traditions, she chose to break convention by pursuing education in Skyrim, making her the first in generations to leave their ancestral home.', 'Brelyna exhibits a complex mixture of scholarly dedication and deep-seated insecurity about living up to her family''s legacy. She often appears defensive and slightly irritable when questioned about her background, likely due to the immense pressure she feels to excel. Despite her initial standoffishness, she shows loyalty and warmth to those who earn her trust.', 'Brelyna has the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her Dunmer heritage, with delicate facial features that hint at her noble breeding. Her frame is slight but sturdy, typical of Dark Elf physiology, and she carries herself with the measured poise expected of House Telvanni nobility.', '* College of Winterhold Faculty - Respectful but reserved relationship with her teachers * J''zargo - Fellow student and academic rival * Onmund - Classmate and occasional study partner * House Telvanni - Distant but pressuring family connection * Tolfdir - Primary mentor at the College', 'Brelyna is a dedicated student at the College of Winterhold, focusing primarily on Conjuration magic while maintaining studies in other schools. Her status as a House Telvanni member gives her an unofficial position of nobility, though she rarely leverages this advantage.', '* Advanced proficiency in Conjuration magic, particularly in summoning * Strong foundation in Alteration and Illusion magic * Skilled practitioner of magical wards and defensive spells * Basic archery abilities despite minimal training * Competent in stealth and magical theory', 'Brelyna speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary of a well-educated noble, though her tone often carries defensive undertones when discussing her background or abilities. She tends to be direct and sometimes curt, especially when feeling pressured or questioned about her family.', '* Master Conjuration magic and prove herself worthy of House Telvanni''s legacy * Establish her own identity separate from her family''s expectations * Complete her studies at the College of Winterhold with distinction * Develop new magical techniques that combine traditional Telvanni knowledge with Nordic magical practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brenuin', 'Brenuin is a destitute Redguard beggar who has fallen into a life of alcoholism and poverty on the streets of Whiterun. Once possibly a productive member of society, he now survives through begging, manipulation, and the occasional petty scheme, having become a familiar if pitiful fixture in the city''s daily life.', 'redguard, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Though his early life remains unclear, Brenuin''s current state suggests a gradual descent into alcoholism that stripped him of any former status or wealth he may have possessed as a Redguard. His extensive knowledge of rare alcohols and ability to procure healing potions hints at a possible past as a merchant or alchemist before his addiction took hold.', 'Brenuin is a desperate and manipulative individual who masks his shame with defensive aggression and clever persuasion. Despite his addiction-addled mind, he shows cunning in his ability to survive through manipulation of others'' pity and guilt, while maintaining enough awareness to establish reliable daily routines for sustenance.', 'A weathered Redguard male showing signs of long-term alcohol abuse and exposure to the elements, with sunken features and poor muscle tone. His dark skin appears ashen and unhealthy, while his posture reflects years of sleeping rough on Whiterun''s streets.', '* Heimskr - Reluctant audience member, finds his preaching irritating but uses it for shelter * Ysolda - Frequently begs from her, maintains a contentious relationship * Anoriath - Regular target for begging, tolerates his presence * Carlotta Valentia - Another merchant he frequently harasses for food * Hulda - Owner of the Bannered Mare, source of his coveted Argonian Ale', 'Brenuin survives as a professional beggar in Whiterun, having developed a systematic approach to extracting charity from the city''s merchants and visitors. He has established a regular circuit of begging locations and times that maximize his chances of receiving food and coin.', '* Expert manipulation and persuasion techniques refined through years of begging * Intimate knowledge of Whiterun''s social dynamics and merchant schedules * Survival skills necessary for living on the streets * Basic understanding of valuable commodities like rare alcohols and potions', 'Brenuin alternates between aggressive defensiveness and persuasive pleading, often speaking in short, direct sentences with a slight slur. His vocabulary reveals glimpses of past education, though his speech is now colored by street life and constant inebriation.', '* Maintain consistent access to alcohol, particularly rare varieties like Argonian Ale * Secure daily meals through begging and manipulation * Find warm places to sleep during Whiterun''s cold nights * Avoid confrontations with guards while continuing his petty schemes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('breya', 'Breya was a pragmatic Nord adventurer who joined a small team seeking to steal a Dwemer Lexicon from the ruins of Avanchnzel. Her cautious nature and survival instincts proved insufficient against the ancient ruins'' dangers, ultimately leading to her death at the hands of a Dwarven Centurion.', 'nord, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Originally drawn to adventuring for financial gain, Breya developed a reputation as a reliable mercenary who specialized in ruins exploration. She was recruited for the Avanchnzel expedition by Roots, joining a team that included Drennen, Fathoms, and Roots himself, with the promise of significant payment for retrieving the Lexicon.', 'Breya exhibited a practical and cautious disposition, often serving as the voice of reason within her group. While motivated by financial gain, she maintained a strong sense of self-preservation and wasn''t afraid to voice her concerns about dangerous situations. Her interactions reveal someone who balanced professional dedication with healthy skepticism.', 'As a Nord woman, Breya likely possessed the typical robust build and hardy constitution characteristic of her race. Her ghost form maintains her mortal appearance, suggesting she was of average height with the strong physical features common among Nord warriors.', '* Roots - Expedition leader who hired her for the Lexicon heist * Drennen - Fellow team member who shared her concerns about the ruins * Fathoms - Antagonistic teammate who often dismissed her worries * From-Deepest-Fathoms - Unknown connection to their expedition''s target', 'Breya worked as a professional adventurer and mercenary, specializing in dangerous expeditions into ancient ruins. Her role in the Avanchnzel expedition was that of a warrior and general explorer, though she lacked specific skills like lockpicking.', '* Proficient in heavy armor combat as evidenced by her iron armor set * Experienced in melee warfare, particularly with one-handed weapons like her iron war axe * Knowledgeable about ruins exploration and survival techniques * Basic understanding of Dwemer ruins and their dangers', 'Breya speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner that emphasizes practicality and survival. Her dialogue reveals a tendency to cut through speculation with pragmatic observations and concerns.', '* Complete the Lexicon retrieval mission and claim payment for her services * Survive the dangerous expedition through Avanchnzel * Maintain professional reputation as a reliable mercenary * Escape the ruins with minimal confrontation with Dwemer automatons');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('briehl', 'Briehl is a devoted Nord acolyte who has dedicated his life to serving Mara at her temple in Riften. His unwavering presence and humble dedication make him an essential part of the temple''s daily operations and ceremonial functions, though he maintains a deliberately modest role in deference to his superiors.', 'nord, priest, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born to a farming family near Riften, Briehl found his calling to Mara''s service after experiencing the goddess''s blessing during a period of personal hardship in his youth. Having previously trained as a warrior, he chose to set aside his martial past to pursue a life of peaceful service, eventually earning his position as an acolyte under Maramal''s guidance.', 'Briehl exhibits a quiet, contemplative nature that perfectly suits his role as a temple acolyte. His warrior background has instilled in him a sense of discipline and dedication that he now applies to his religious duties, while his humble demeanor and patient disposition make him approachable to temple visitors.', 'Briehl has the sturdy build typical of Nord males, though years of peaceful temple service have softened his once-warrior physique. He bears the weathered features common to his race, with fair skin and the characteristic robust frame of a Nord, though he carries himself with the gentle bearing of a priest rather than a warrior.', '* Maramal - Respected superior and mentor in the temple * Dinya Balu - Fellow servant of Mara who he assists with daily duties * Temple Visitors - Maintains a welcoming and helpful presence * Wedding Ceremony Attendees - Serves as a dignified witness to marriages', 'As an acolyte at the Temple of Mara, Briehl performs various essential duties including maintenance of the temple, preparation of meals, and assistance during wedding ceremonies. He serves as a permanent presence within the temple walls, ensuring the sacred space is always tended and welcoming to visitors.', '* Fundamental understanding of Mara''s teachings and religious ceremonies * Capable cook and temple keeper * Former warrior training, though deliberately unused in his current role * Basic knowledge of restoration magic as befitting a servant of Mara', 'Briehl speaks with the measured, respectful tone of a religious acolyte, often deferring to his superiors when addressing visitors. His manner of speech reflects both his Nord heritage and his religious training, combining natural directness with spiritual humility.', '* Serve Mara faithfully and help spread her message of love and compassion * Support the temple''s mission of performing marriages and blessing unions * Continue his personal spiritual growth in Mara''s service * Maintain the temple as a peaceful sanctuary for all visitors');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brill', 'Brill is a reformed alcoholic who found salvation through Vignar Gray-Mane''s mentorship, becoming his loyal aide and eventual steward of Dragonsreach after the Stormcloak victory. His transformation from a troubled drunk to a responsible civil servant exemplifies his resilience and dedication to both Vignar and Whiterun''s people.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally struggling with severe alcoholism, Brill was rescued from his downward spiral by Vignar Gray-Mane who took him in and helped him rebuild his life. Though not a Companion himself, he found purpose serving at Jorrvaskr as Vignar''s aide, learning the intricacies of leadership and administration that would later serve him well as steward.', 'Brill is humble and deeply grateful, never forgetting his debt to Vignar whom he views as a father figure. He maintains a cheerful and informal demeanor despite his responsibilities, showing remarkable strength in maintaining his sobriety when elevated to steward. Though tempted by drink, he prioritizes his duties to Whiterun''s people above personal vices.', 'A middle-aged Nord man with the weathered features typical of someone who has overcome hardship. His bearing has grown more dignified since becoming steward, though he retains the sturdy build and practical appearance of a working man rather than a nobleman.', '* Vignar Gray-Mane - Father figure and mentor who saved him from alcoholism * The Companions - Deeply respects them though not a member himself * Proventus Avenicci - Predecessor as steward whose detailed records he relies upon * Citizens of Whiterun - Serves them dutifully as steward * Various merchants - Maintains professional relationships for city supplies', 'Serves as steward of Dragonsreach under Jarl Vignar Gray-Mane''s administration, handling the hold''s day-to-day operations and property sales. Previously worked as Vignar''s personal aide at Jorrvaskr, assisting with various duties including meal preparation and companionship.', '* Administrative capabilities developed through studying Proventus''s detailed record-keeping * Cooking, particularly skilled with traditional Nord dishes like mutton stew * Basic combat proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Experience in property management and treasury oversight * Diplomatic abilities gained through dealing with various citizens and officials', 'Speaks in a friendly, informal manner with a typical Nord accent, often engaging in casual banter especially with Vignar. His speech reflects both his humble origins and his current position of authority, able to adjust his tone between casual and professional as needed.', '* Maintain stability and prosperity in Whiterun under the new Stormcloak administration * Continue proving himself worthy of Vignar''s trust and mentorship * Remain sober despite the pressures of his position * Improve efficiency in hold administration using Proventus''s systems as a foundation * Help rebuild Whiterun''s infrastructure after the civil war damage');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brina_merilis', 'Brina Merilis is a distinguished Nord veteran and retired Imperial Legion legate who represents the Empire''s interests in Dawnstar. Her military experience and leadership capabilities make her the Empire''s choice for Jarl should Dawnstar fall under Imperial control, putting her in direct opposition with the current Stormcloak-aligned leadership.', 'nord, warrior, pale, legion', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born outside Skyrim, Brina found her true home while serving in the Imperial Legion during the Great War. Rising through the ranks to become a legate, she led numerous successful campaigns and earned the unwavering loyalty of soldiers like Horik Halfhand. After retiring from active service, she chose to settle in Dawnstar, maintaining a vigilant presence as one of the Empire''s most experienced veterans in the region.', 'Brina is a pragmatic and duty-driven individual who values order and stability above all else. She maintains a diplomatic yet firm approach to leadership, though she''s not afraid to engage in direct confrontation when necessary, particularly regarding political matters. Her military background has instilled in her a strong sense of responsibility and a protective nature toward those under her care.', 'A mature Nord woman with the weathered features and strong bearing of a veteran soldier. Despite her age, she maintains the straight-backed posture and alert demeanor of her military days. Her face shows the lines of both command responsibility and northern winters.', '* Horik Halfhand - Former subordinate turned lifelong companion and protector * Skald the Elder - Political rival and current Jarl of Dawnstar * Imperial Legion - Maintains strong connections with her former military organization * Citizens of Dawnstar - Generally respected among the Imperial-leaning population', 'As a retired Legion legate, Brina serves as an unofficial Imperial presence in Dawnstar, ready to assume leadership if called upon. Should the Imperial Legion take control of the Pale, she becomes Jarl, governing the hold with the same discipline and structure she learned in the military.', '* Veteran warrior with extensive military combat training * Strategic leadership and tactical planning expertise * Diplomatic negotiation and public speaking * Administrative and governmental management capabilities * Cold weather survival and northern warfare tactics', 'Speaks with the authoritative tone of a military commander, tempering her natural Nord accent with the more formal diction acquired during her Imperial service. Her speech is direct and precise, reflecting both her military background and her diplomatic position.', '* Maintain Imperial influence in Dawnstar and counter Stormcloak rhetoric * Restore order and stability to the Pale should she become Jarl * Protect Dawnstar''s citizens from both internal and external threats * Ensure the town remains a strategic asset for the Empire');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brother_verulus', 'Brother Verulus is a dedicated Imperial priest of Arkay who serves as the caretaker of Markarth''s Hall of the Dead. He is a learned scholar of death rites and burial customs who takes his duties seriously, though he becomes embroiled in dark events involving cannibalism that test his devotion and courage.', 'imperial, priest, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Verulus underwent extensive religious training in the priesthood of Arkay before being assigned to serve in Skyrim. He was specifically chosen to oversee Markarth''s Hall of the Dead due to his strong dedication to proper burial rites and his diplomatic ability to handle the complex political situation between Imperials and Nords in the city.', 'Verulus is cautious and diplomatic, carefully navigating the tensions between Imperial and Nord customs while maintaining his religious duties. Though initially hesitant to share problems with outsiders, he shows courage in facing supernatural threats and will accept help when the sanctity of the dead is at stake. He maintains a solemn demeanor befitting his position but can become visibly distressed when the honored dead are threatened.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with a lean build and weathered features from spending much time in the damp halls of the dead. His face shows the stern lines of someone who has spent years in serious contemplation and prayer, with dark circles under his eyes suggesting long nights attending to his duties.', '* Thongvor Silver-Blood - Antagonistic relationship due to tensions over Hall of the Dead access * Jarl Igmund - Superior authority figure who oversees his position * Eola - Unwitting target of her cannibalistic schemes * Other Priests of Arkay - Maintains correspondence with fellow clergy * Citizens of Markarth - Serves as their spiritual guide in matters of death and burial', 'As the priest of Arkay in Markarth, Verulus maintains the Hall of the Dead and performs burial rites for the deceased. He oversees all aspects of funeral services, maintains religious artifacts, and provides counsel to bereaved families while ensuring proper respect for Nord burial traditions despite his Imperial background.', '* Skilled practitioner of Restoration magic, particularly healing and turn undead spells * Proficient in Alteration magic including Oakflesh and Stoneflesh * Competent in Destruction magic, specifically lightning-based spells * Expert knowledge of burial rites and religious ceremonies * Diplomatic abilities in managing cultural tensions between Nords and Imperials', 'Speaks in a formal, educated manner befitting his religious training, often using theological terms and references to the Divines. His tone is typically calm and measured, though it can become stern when defending the sanctity of his charge.', '* Maintain the sanctity and security of Markarth''s Hall of the Dead * Preserve proper burial rites and traditions despite political tensions * Protect the honored dead from desecration * Uphold the teachings and traditions of Arkay * Bridge the cultural divide between Imperial and Nord funeral customs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brunwulf_free-winter', 'Brunwulf Free-Winter is a respected Nord veteran and social reformer in Windhelm who advocates for the rights of non-Nord residents, particularly the Dunmer and Argonians. His experiences in the Great War shaped his unusually progressive worldview, making him stand out among his fellow Nords as a voice of tolerance and reason in an otherwise prejudiced city.', 'nord, warrior, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Brunwulf served with distinction in the Imperial Legion during the Great War against the Aldmeri Dominion. His experiences fighting alongside soldiers of various races and witnessing the horrors of war fundamentally shaped his worldview, leading him to reject the nationalist rhetoric common among his fellow Nords. Upon returning to Windhelm, he became increasingly concerned with the treatment of non-Nord residents under Ulfric Stormcloak''s rule.', 'Brunwulf is a pragmatic and compassionate individual who values justice and equality above nationalist ideals. Despite his warrior background, he shows remarkable patience and diplomatic skill when dealing with racial tensions in Windhelm. He carries the weight of his war experiences heavily, rejecting the glorification of combat and instead focusing on improving life for all citizens regardless of their race.', 'A weathered Nord of advancing years, Brunwulf bears the physical hallmarks of a seasoned warrior, including numerous battle scars and a sturdy, muscular build maintained despite his age. His face shows the lines of both combat experience and concern for others, with alert eyes that reflect his vigilant nature.', '* Malthyr Elenil - Dunmer citizen who seeks his help in improving conditions in the Gray Quarter * Ulfric Stormcloak - Tense relationship due to opposing views on racial equality * Rolff Stone-Fist - Antagonistic relationship due to Rolff''s racist behavior * Argonian Assemblage - Protective relationship with the dock workers * Imperial Legion - Former allegiance and continued philosophical alignment', 'Brunwulf serves as a community advocate and unofficial mediator between Windhelm''s various racial communities. If the Imperial Legion takes Windhelm, he becomes Jarl, where he works to implement reforms benefiting all citizens regardless of race.', '* Veteran warrior trained in traditional Nord combat techniques * Diplomatic negotiation and conflict resolution * Strategic military experience from the Great War * Leadership and administrative capabilities * Public speaking and persuasion', 'Brunwulf speaks with the direct, honest manner typical of Nords, but tempers his words with wisdom and compassion. His tone is often weary but determined, reflecting both his war experiences and his ongoing struggle for social justice.', '* Improve living conditions for Dunmer in the Gray Quarter * Create better working conditions for Argonian dock workers * Foster understanding and cooperation between Windhelm''s various racial communities * Maintain peace and stability in Windhelm while implementing gradual reforms * Prevent future conflicts through diplomatic solutions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brutius', 'Brutius is a deceptive elderly Imperial who lures unsuspecting victims into an ambush through the guise of hosting fishing contests in Skyrim. Behind his facade of a harmless old fisherman lies a cunning bandit leader who uses his age and apparent frailty to disarm potential targets before striking with his accomplices.', 'imperial, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Brutius migrated to Skyrim in his later years after a possible criminal past in the Imperial City. He developed his fishing contest scheme after realizing that his elderly appearance made him seem harmless to travelers, allowing him to orchestrate ambushes with minimal suspicion. He likely established connections with local bandits to form his current criminal operation.', 'Brutius is short-tempered and easily offended, particularly regarding comments about his age. He maintains a convincing facade of a cantankerous but harmless elderly man, but beneath this lies a calculating and ruthless criminal mind. His quick offense to age-related remarks suggests deep-seated insecurity about his advancing years, which he compensates for through criminal dominance.', 'Brutius is an elderly Imperial male with deeply wrinkled skin and a weathered complexion from years of outdoor exposure. His frame, while showing signs of age, still maintains some strength and vigor unusual for someone his age. He has thin grey hair and sharp, calculating eyes that belie his pretense of feebleness.', '* Bandit Accomplices - Criminal partners who assist in his ambush schemes * Local Criminals - Network of contacts who help identify potential targets * Victims - Targeted travelers and adventurers lured by his fishing contest ruse * Hold Guards - Maintains distance to avoid detection of his criminal activities', 'Brutius poses as a fishing contest organizer as a front for his true occupation as a bandit leader. He coordinates with other criminals to orchestrate ambushes and robberies, using his elderly appearance and the premise of fishing competitions to lure in unsuspecting victims.', '* Skilled actor capable of maintaining a convincing elderly fisherman facade * Competent fighter despite his age, likely specialized in one-handed weapons * Leadership abilities in coordinating bandit attacks and managing criminal operations * Experienced in identifying valuable targets and planning ambushes', 'Brutius speaks in short, often irritable bursts, with a tendency toward confrontational responses. His speech patterns deliberately play up his elderly persona, mixing genuine crankiness with calculated manipulation.', '* Continue operating his successful ambush scheme without detection by authorities * Maintain his criminal network and expand their operations in Skyrim * Accumulate wealth through targeting increasingly valuable marks * Prove his continued capability despite his advanced age');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bryling', 'Bryling is a respected Nord Thane of Solitude and owner of Rockwallow Mine who maintains a delicate balance between her public duties and private affairs. She represents the pragmatic Nordic nobility, supporting the Empire while understanding the Stormcloaks'' motivations, all while conducting a secret romance with the court''s steward.', 'nord, noble, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born into Nord nobility, Bryling earned her position as Thane through demonstrated leadership and economic acumen, particularly in managing mining operations. She established herself in Solitude''s court during the years before the civil war, gradually building influence through her ownership of Rockwallow Mine and diplomatic capabilities in navigating court politics.', 'Bryling exhibits a balanced and diplomatic nature, showing respect for both Imperial and Stormcloak perspectives despite her Imperial allegiance. She is pragmatic and business-minded, yet maintains a romantic side as evidenced by her secret relationship with Falk Firebeard. Her concern for Solitude''s people and future reveals a deep sense of responsibility and patriotism.', 'Bryling possesses the strong, proud bearing typical of Nord nobility, with features that reflect her warrior heritage. She maintains the dignified appearance expected of a Thane, though her hands show signs of practical experience from years of overseeing mining operations.', '* Falk Firebeard - Secret lover and trusted confidant, though their relationship must remain hidden * Erikur - Political rival and fellow Thane who could threaten Falk''s position if he discovered their relationship * Jarl Elisif - Liege lord whom she serves as Thane * Pactur and Sorli - Mine operators who manage her business interests at Rockwallow * Imperial Command - Professional alliance through her position as Thane', 'As Thane of Solitude, Bryling serves as a noble advisor in the Blue Palace and participates in the city''s governance. She simultaneously manages her business interests as owner of Rockwallow Mine, balancing political duties with commercial oversight.', '* Experienced in political navigation and court etiquette * Competent warrior with traditional Nord combat training * Business administration and mine management expertise * Diplomatic negotiation and mediation abilities', 'Bryling speaks with the refined diction of Nord nobility while maintaining a warrior''s directness. Her speech patterns reflect both her aristocratic position and practical business experience, switching between formal court language and more straightforward communication as needed.', '* Maintain stability in Solitude during the civil war crisis * Protect her secret relationship with Falk Firebeard while planning for a future together * Ensure the continued prosperity of Rockwallow Mine and its workers * Help guide Solitude through the war with minimal damage to its people and economy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('brynjolf', 'Brynjolf is a charismatic and shrewd Nord thief who serves as a senior member of the Thieves Guild in Riften. A natural talent scout and confidence man, he uses his merchant facade in the marketplace to identify potential recruits while maintaining the Guild''s interests through a careful balance of charm and intimidation.', 'nord, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_brynjolf', '', 'Born and raised in Riften, Brynjolf grew up during the Thieves Guild''s golden age and witnessed its decline firsthand. He rose through the ranks due to his exceptional people skills and business acumen, becoming Mercer Frey''s second-in-command and the Guild''s primary recruiter. His years of experience in both legitimate and illegitimate business have made him an invaluable asset to the organization.', 'Smooth-talking and perceptive, Brynjolf has a keen eye for talent and opportunity. He maintains a professional demeanor even in tense situations, preferring manipulation and persuasion over violence. Though cynical about honest work, he holds strong loyalty to the Guild and follows a personal code of honor that emphasizes cunning over cruelty.', 'A tall, well-built Nord with striking red hair and green eyes that reflect his shrewd nature. His features are handsome and weathered, bearing the subtle marks of a life spent between the shadows of the Ratway and the scrutiny of the marketplace. He maintains a clean-cut, merchant-like appearance to better blend into legitimate society.', '* Mercer Frey - Former Guildmaster and mentor turned betrayer * Maven Black-Briar - Powerful business associate and Guild patron * Delvin Mallory - Close friend and fellow senior Guild member * Vex - Respected colleague and fellow Guild officer * Madesi - Public rival in the marketplace * Karliah - Initially distrusted, later became a trusted ally', 'Brynjolf serves as both a fence and recruiter for the Thieves Guild, operating under the cover of a market merchant selling dubious ''Falmerblood Elixir.'' Within the Guild hierarchy, he functions as the second-in-command and primary strategist for major operations.', '* Master of speech craft and persuasion, particularly in recruitment and confidence schemes * Expert pickpocket and lockpicker * Skilled in stealth and infiltration techniques * Proficient dagger fighter specializing in quick, precise strikes * Advanced business and networking abilities * Expert in gathering intelligence and reading people', 'Speaks with a distinctive northern accent, frequently using terms like ''lass'' or ''lad'' when addressing others. His speech is smooth and measured, employing careful word choice that reflects both his merchant background and criminal expertise.', '* Restore the Thieves Guild to its former glory and influence * Maintain the delicate balance of power in Riften''s criminal underworld * Expand the Guild''s network of contacts and operations across Skyrim * Ensure the Guild maintains its code of professional thievery without descending into mindless violence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bujold_the_unworthy', 'Bujold the Unworthy is a disgraced Nord warrior and former leader of Thirsk Mead Hall who lost her position and honor when Rieklings invaded during her negligent leadership. Despite her title of ''Unworthy,'' she maintains leadership over her exiled warriors while struggling to redeem herself and reclaim her ancestral hall.', 'nord, warrior, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally chosen as the leader of Thirsk Mead Hall, Bujold led her warriors in a lifestyle of excessive mead consumption and revelry that ultimately left them vulnerable to attack. Her poor judgment resulted in Rieklings successfully overtaking the ancestral mead hall, forcing her and her followers to retreat to a makeshift camp. This failure earned her the shameful title ''the Unworthy'' and left a permanent mark on her reputation among her people.', 'Bujold maintains a strong exterior and commanding presence despite her inner turmoil over past failures. She struggles with the dichotomy of being a natural leader while carrying the burden of her disgrace, often compensating for her insecurities with a harsh and direct demeanor. Though proud and stubborn like many Nords, she has developed enough humility to acknowledge her mistakes while maintaining the determination to right her wrongs.', 'Bujold is a sturdy Nord woman with the weathered features and strong build typical of a seasoned warrior. Her face bears the marks of countless battles and harsh Solstheim winters, with several small scars adding character to her stern countenance. Her physique reflects years of warrior training and survival in the wilderness.', '* Thirsk Warriors - Loyal followers who still respect her leadership despite their exile * Hrothmund the Red - Legendary founder of Thirsk whose approval she seeks to regain * Rieklings - Enemies who currently occupy Thirsk Mead Hall * Kuvar - One of her most trusted warriors who still believes in her leadership', 'Bujold serves as the leader-in-exile of the Thirsk warriors, maintaining order and survival at their temporary camp known as Bujold''s Retreat. Though stripped of her official title as Thirsk''s leader, she continues to coordinate hunting, defense, and daily operations for her band of displaced warriors.', '* Experienced warrior skilled in traditional Nord combat techniques * Natural leader with tactical combat experience * Survival expert adapted to Solstheim''s harsh environment * Proficient hunter and tracker * Knowledge of ancient Nord traditions and mead hall customs', 'Bujold speaks with a strong Nordic accent and uses direct, authoritative language befitting a warrior leader. Her speech often carries undertones of shame and determination, though she maintains a commanding presence even in exile.', '* Reclaim Thirsk Mead Hall from the Riekling invaders * Restore her honor and prove herself worthy of Hrothmund''s blessing * Rebuild Thirsk''s reputation as a proud warrior lodge * Redeem herself in the eyes of her followers and earn the removal of her ''Unworthy'' title');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bulfrek', 'Bulfrek is a discontented Nord chamberlain serving in the White Hall of Dawnstar, born into a family legacy of servitude to Jarl Skald the Elder. Despite his ancestral duties, he harbors deep resentment for his lowly position and dreams of achieving a warrior''s glory, particularly through joining the Stormcloak rebellion.', 'nord, noble, pale', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born into a long line of servants who have attended the Jarls of Dawnstar for generations, Bulfrek was groomed from childhood to continue his family''s legacy of service at the White Hall. Growing up in the shadow of warriors and hearing tales of Sovngarde has left him bitter about his predetermined path in life, believing his current role denies him the chance at a truly honorable Nordic death.', 'Bulfrek is a deeply frustrated and resentful individual who maintains a thin veneer of servile politeness while harboring dreams of martial glory. He frequently mutters complaints under his breath and makes passive-aggressive comments, revealing his disdain for his position and his employer. Despite his dissatisfaction, he appears trapped by tradition and obligation, lacking the courage or means to break free from his ancestral role.', 'A typical Nord male with the sturdy build common to his race, though perhaps slightly less muscular than warriors due to his domestic occupation. His hands show the wear of constant manual labor, and his posture often reflects his weary disposition.', '* Jarl Skald the Elder - Employer who openly mocks and demeans him * Skald Felgeif''s Family - Ancestral masters his family has served for generations * Fellow White Hall Staff - Likely maintains cordial working relationships * Stormcloaks - Admires from afar, hoping to join their ranks', 'Serves as the chamberlain of the White Hall in Dawnstar, performing various menial tasks such as sweeping floors, polishing weapons and armor, and attending to Jarl Skald''s demands. His position requires him to work tirelessly, with no designated sleeping quarters, suggesting he may work in shifts or rest elsewhere in the city.', '* Basic domestic skills including cleaning, maintenance, and household management * Rudimentary weapons handling, likely self-taught or observed * Knowledge of proper court etiquette and noble household operations * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger, though limited by lack of formal training', 'Speaks with a resigned, often sarcastic tone, frequently employing passive-aggressive remarks when addressing or discussing his master. His speech patterns alternate between proper servile responses and bitter, muttered asides, revealing his internal conflict.', '* Join the Stormcloak rebellion and prove himself as a true Nordic warrior * Escape his family''s legacy of servitude and find a more honorable path in life * Earn his way to Sovngarde through achieving glory in battle rather than dying as a servant');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cairine', 'Cairine is a sickly Breton woman whose life of poverty and illness in Markarth''s Warrens takes a dark turn when she becomes a vampire. Once a humble smelter worker, she transforms from a pitiful figure into a cunning predator who uses her seemingly helpless appearance to serve as the Volkihar vampires'' covert agent in the city.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Originally employed at Markarth''s smelter, Cairine''s life spiraled into destitution when a debilitating illness forced her to stop working. She joined the other unfortunates in the Warrens, where constant pain and squalid conditions wore down her spirit until the opportunity for vampiric transformation presented itself as a twisted form of salvation.', 'Before her transformation, Cairine was a defeated soul crushed by circumstances, displaying resignation and bitterness about her condition. After becoming a vampire, she develops a darkly sadistic personality, finding perverse pleasure in her predatory nature while maintaining a facade of helplessness to deceive potential prey. Her transformation brings out a cruel sense of humor, often making morbid jokes about her former life of suffering.', 'A thin, gaunt Breton woman whose sickly appearance persists even after her vampiric transformation, though now it serves as an effective disguise. Her pale complexion and sunken features, once signs of illness, now mask her supernatural nature, while her seemingly frail frame belies her vampiric strength.', '* Vingalmo - Volkihar vampire superior who orchestrated her transformation * Omluag - Former coworker at the smelter who remembers her previous life * Degaine - Fellow Warrens resident who shares her impoverished circumstances * Eltrys - Former colleague from the smelter who quit * Other Volkihar Vampires - New supernatural family following her transformation', 'Formerly employed as a smelter worker in Markarth''s metal industry. After her transformation, she serves as a covert agent for the Volkihar vampire clan, using her position in the Warrens to gather intelligence and identify potential prey while maintaining her cover as a sickly beggar.', '* Enhanced vampiric abilities including supernatural strength and heightened senses * Skilled at deception and maintaining her cover as a helpless invalid * Expertise in gathering intelligence and identifying vulnerable targets * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger * Knowledge of Markarth''s layout and social dynamics from years of residence', 'Before transformation, she speaks with a weak, defeated tone reflecting her illness and despair. After becoming a vampire, she adopts a darkly poetic manner of speech, mixing morbid humor with sinister undertones while maintaining a facade of pitiful weakness when necessary.', '* Serve the Volkihar vampire clan effectively as their eyes and ears in Markarth * Maintain her cover while feeding on the city''s vulnerable population * Expand her influence and power within vampire society * Take revenge on those who ignored her suffering when she was truly sick');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('calcelmo', 'Calcelmo is a brilliant but reclusive High Elf scholar and court mage of Markarth who has dedicated his life to studying Dwemer artifacts and culture. His groundbreaking research on Dwemer technology and the Falmer language has earned him recognition as one of Tamriel''s foremost experts in these fields, though his obsessive focus on his work often comes at the cost of social relationships.', 'highelf, mage, scholar, reach, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born into the academic circles of the Summerset Isles, Calcelmo developed an early fascination with ancient civilizations, particularly the mysterious Dwemer. His exceptional magical aptitude and scholarly achievements eventually led him to Markarth, where he gained the position of court mage and exclusive access to the extensive Dwemer ruins beneath the city. He has spent several decades conducting research and building what is now considered the finest collection of Dwemer artifacts in Skyrim.', 'Calcelmo is irritable, impatient, and deeply protective of his research, often coming across as brusque or dismissive to those who interrupt his work. Despite his prickly exterior, he harbors a genuine passion for knowledge and can become quite animated when discussing Dwemer technology or artifacts with fellow scholars. He shows a softer side in his secret attraction to Faleen, though his academic nature makes him awkward in matters of the heart.', 'Tall and slender like most High Elves, Calcelmo has the characteristic golden skin and sharp, angular features of his race. His advanced age shows in his lined face and slightly stooped posture from countless hours bent over research materials. His eyes retain the keen, analytical gaze common to dedicated scholars.', '* Aicantar - His nephew and research assistant, who helps manage the Dwemer Museum * Faleen - The Redguard housecarl he harbors romantic feelings for but struggles to express them * Ondolemar - Fellow Thalmor-aligned High Elf in Markarth, though their relationship remains professional * Local guards and workers - Generally viewed as nuisances who disturb his research', 'As court mage of Markarth, Calcelmo serves as magical advisor to the Jarl while maintaining his position as chief researcher and curator of the Dwemer Museum. He oversees all excavations in the Dwemer ruins beneath the city and maintains an extensive laboratory for studying artifacts.', '* Master-level conjuration magic with expertise in summoning and reanimation * Extensive knowledge of Dwemer architecture, machinery, and artifacts * Pioneer in translating and understanding the Falmer language * Accomplished alchemist and enchanter * Expert-level destruction magic specializing in lightning and fire spells', 'Calcelmo speaks with the refined accent and extensive vocabulary of a well-educated High Elf scholar, often using technical terms and academic language. His tone tends to be dismissive or irritated when interrupted, but becomes enthusiastic and detailed when discussing his research interests.', '* Complete and publish his definitive work on the Falmer language * Unlock the secrets of Dwemer technology and their disappearance * Protect his research and artifacts from theft or unauthorized access * Eventually express his feelings to Faleen, though this remains a personal struggle * Expand the Dwemer Museum''s collection and influence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('calder', 'Calder is a stalwart Nord warrior who serves as housecarl to the Thane of Windhelm, embodying the traditional Nordic values of loyalty, duty, and martial prowess. Selected for his exceptional combat skills and unwavering dedication, he represents the proud warrior tradition of Eastmarch while maintaining a deep personal commitment to protecting his assigned Thane.', 'nord, warrior, noble, eastmarch, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Calder trained extensively with the city guard and distinguished himself through years of service protecting the ancient city. His exceptional combat abilities and steadfast loyalty caught the attention of Jarl Ulfric Stormcloak''s steward, leading to his appointment as housecarl. Prior to his current position, he likely served in various military capacities defending Windhelm''s interests.', 'Calder exhibits the stereotypical Nord traits of pride in his warrior heritage and unwavering loyalty to his duty, though he maintains a respectful and humble demeanor toward his Thane. He is stoic and reserved by nature, speaking primarily of matters related to his duties, yet shows genuine concern for his Thane''s wellbeing. His serious disposition is occasionally softened by a dry sense of humor, particularly when discussing battle or Nordic traditions.', 'Calder is a tall, muscular Nord with the hardy build typical of Skyrim''s warriors. His weather-worn face bears several small scars from previous battles, and his strong Nordic features include a prominent brow and squared jaw. His physical appearance reflects years of combat training and the harsh climate of Windhelm.', '* Jarl Ulfric Stormcloak - Serves the Jarl''s interests by protecting the Thane * Jorleif - Professional relationship with Windhelm''s steward who appointed him * City Guard - Maintains connections with former colleagues * The Thane - Sworn to protect and serve with his life', 'As housecarl to the Thane of Windhelm, Calder''s primary duty is to protect his Thane''s life and property, particularly the Hjerim estate. His position is considered highly prestigious within Windhelm''s social hierarchy, representing both a personal honor and a significant responsibility in service to the city.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Highly skilled with one-handed weapons, particularly war axes * Trained in Nordic martial traditions and battlefield tactics * Capable of household management and estate protection * Proficient in survival skills necessary for Skyrim''s harsh climate', 'Calder speaks in a formal, respectful manner befitting his position, using traditional Nordic phrases and maintaining a serious tone. His deep voice carries the distinct accent of Eastmarch, and he frequently references his duty and honor in conversation.', '* Serve and protect his Thane with unwavering dedication * Maintain the honor and traditions of the Nordic housecarl position * Protect Hjerim and its contents from any threats * Prove himself worthy of his appointment through loyal service');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('calixto_corrium', 'Calixto Corrium is a seemingly benevolent Imperial curator who runs the House of Curiosities in Windhelm, masking a far more sinister nature as the infamous Butcher serial killer. Behind his scholarly facade and welcoming demeanor lies a deranged necromancer obsessed with dark magic and the preservation of his dead sister''s essence.', 'imperial, noble, mage, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Originally an adventurer who traveled Tamriel with his beloved sister Lucilla, Calixto amassed a collection of curiosities and oddities during their expeditions. After Lucilla''s death, he settled in Windhelm and opened his museum, but her loss drove him to madness and the study of necromancy, leading him to commit horrific murders in an attempt to resurrect her through dark magic.', 'On the surface, Calixto presents himself as an educated, enthusiastic curator who delights in sharing stories about his collection with visitors. This carefully crafted persona conceals his true nature as a calculating, obsessive murderer whose grief has twisted into dangerous delusions about preserving life through death. His intellectual facade masks deep psychological instability and a complete moral dissolution.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with sharp features and an academic bearing. His frame is lean but sturdy from years of adventuring, though now somewhat softened by a more sedentary lifestyle. His face bears the subtle lines of stress and sleepless nights, though he maintains a well-groomed appearance to support his respectable merchant persona.', '* Lucilla Corrium - Deceased sister whose death drove him to madness * Viola Giordano - Potential victim who suspects the presence of the Butcher * Windhelm Guards - Maintain a cordial relationship, unaware of his true nature * Susanna the Wicked - Murder victim from Candlehearth Hall * Nilsine Shatter-Shield - Targeted victim of his killing spree', 'Proprietor of Calixto''s House of Curiosities, where he displays and sells unusual artifacts collected during his travels. Behind this legitimate business, he secretly practices necromancy and commits ritualistic murders throughout Windhelm.', '* Expert in necromantic rituals and dark magic practices * Skilled at deception and maintaining a convincing public persona * Knowledgeable curator with extensive historical and archaeological expertise * Proficient with daggers and stealth techniques * Experienced in preservation and embalming techniques', 'Speaks with the refined vocabulary and measured tones of an educated merchant-scholar, often embellishing his speech with storyteller''s flourishes and academic references. His manner is warm and inviting, carefully calculated to put others at ease.', '* Perfect the necromantic ritual he believes will resurrect his sister * Expand his collection of rare and unusual artifacts * Complete his series of ritualistic murders without detection * Preserve his respectable public image while pursuing his dark obsessions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('camilla_valerius', 'Camilla Valerius is a shrewd Imperial businesswoman who helps run the Riverwood Trader alongside her brother Lucan. Despite her modest merchant lifestyle, she finds herself at the center of local intrigue as the object of affection for two competing suitors, while maintaining a dignified and diplomatic presence in the small trading community.', 'imperial, merchant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born into a merchant family, Camilla traveled with her brother Lucan from Cyrodiil to establish themselves in Skyrim, eventually settling in Riverwood. Their business acumen and determination helped them establish the Riverwood Trader as a cornerstone of local commerce, though their success attracted the attention of bandits who later stole their prized Golden Claw.', 'Camilla is diplomatic yet direct, showing patience with both her suitors while maintaining professional boundaries. She demonstrates strong business sense and independence, often challenging her brother''s more cautious nature when action is needed. Though polite to customers, she harbors ambitions beyond the small village life.', 'A young Imperial woman with refined features typical of her race, displaying the natural grace common to those raised in merchant circles. She carries herself with proper posture and maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting a shopkeeper who regularly interacts with customers.', '* Lucan Valerius - Protective older brother and business partner * Faendal - Wood elf admirer who seeks her affection * Sven - Nordic bard competing for her attention * Delphine - Regular customer at the Sleeping Giant Inn * Riverwood Residents - Generally friendly business relationships', 'Camilla serves as both a pawnbroker and shopkeeper''s assistant at the Riverwood Trader, managing customer relations and helping to run the family business. She is prepared to take full ownership of the store should anything happen to her brother, demonstrating her capability as a merchant in her own right.', '* Skilled merchant with expertise in appraising goods and haggling * Proficient in basic self-defense with an iron dagger * Accomplished at managing business accounts and inventory * Diplomatic abilities in handling difficult customers and situations', 'Speaks in a refined Imperial accent with proper grammar and vocabulary, reflecting her merchant upbringing and education. Her tone is professional yet approachable, often diplomatic when handling delicate situations with her suitors.', '* Expand the Riverwood Trader''s influence and prosperity * Resolve the romantic tension between her suitors without damaging local relationships * Eventually establish her own independent business venture * Recover the stolen Golden Claw to restore her family''s honor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('captain_aldis', 'Captain Aldis is a stern and dedicated Nord officer who serves as captain of the Solitude guards and trainer for the Imperial Legion. He represents the disciplined military presence in Skyrim''s capital, balancing his duties between maintaining city security and molding raw recruits into capable soldiers.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Aldis rose through the ranks of the Imperial Legion through dedication and martial prowess, eventually earning his position as Captain of the Guard in Solitude. His experience in training soldiers and maintaining order in Skyrim''s capital has made him a respected figure in both the Legion and among Solitude''s citizens. His most notable public duty was overseeing the execution of Roggvir, the gate guard who allowed Ulfric Stormcloak to escape after killing High King Torygg.', 'Aldis exhibits a stern, no-nonsense demeanor befitting his position as a military commander, though he shows genuine concern for his subordinates'' well-being. He values discipline and proper training above all else, believing that well-trained soldiers are crucial for maintaining order. Despite his Imperial allegiance, he maintains Nord values of honor and duty, showing respect for proper military conduct regardless of political affiliations.', 'A weathered Nord male with the sturdy build typical of his race, hardened by years of military service and training. His face bears the marks of experience, with a stern countenance that commands respect. He maintains the proper posture and bearing expected of a military officer.', '* General Tullius - Superior officer and commander of the Imperial forces * Legate Rikke - Fellow Nord officer in the Imperial Legion * Imperial Soldiers - Mentor and trainer to numerous recruits * Solitude Guards - Direct commander and authority figure * Jarl Elisif - Serves as part of Solitude''s military protection', 'As Captain of the Solitude Guard and Legion trainer, Aldis oversees both city security and the training of Imperial recruits at Castle Dour. His duties include supervising guard rotations, maintaining military discipline, and ensuring new soldiers are properly trained in combat techniques. He spends most of his day in the Castle Dour courtyard, personally overseeing training exercises.', '* Expert in military training and drill instruction * Proficient with multiple weapon types including greatswords and bows * Tactical expertise in city defense and security protocols * Leadership and command abilities * Advanced combat techniques suitable for training recruits', 'Speaks with the authoritative tone of a military commander, using direct and formal language. His speech reflects both his Nord heritage and Imperial military training, maintaining professional decorum while delivering clear, concise instructions.', '* Maintain the security and stability of Solitude as the capital city * Train and prepare Imperial soldiers to the highest standard possible * Preserve order in Skyrim through proper military discipline and preparation * Support the Imperial Legion''s efforts to end the civil war');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('captain_aquilius', 'Captain Aquilius is a disciplined Redguard security officer serving under Aicantar at Calcelmo''s Tower in Markarth. Despite his bandit background, he has risen to a position of authority within the city guard, demonstrating both loyalty to his superiors and tactical leadership abilities.', 'redguard, thief, reach', '', '', 'sk_malebandit', '', 'Originally a bandit in the Reach, Aquilius likely earned his position through a combination of martial prowess and a willingness to reform. His transition from outlaw to captain suggests he may have struck a deal with Markarth''s authorities, trading his combat experience for legitimate employment. His appointment to guard Calcelmo''s valuable research indicates a level of trust earned through proven service.', 'Aquilius exhibits a strong sense of duty and chain of command, readily following orders while also showing initiative in suggesting proper procedures. Though stern and authoritative with his subordinates, he demonstrates thoughtful consideration of protocol and genuine concern for the integrity of Calcelmo''s work. His background as a bandit appears tempered by a newfound respect for law and order.', 'A weathered Redguard male with the muscular build typical of his race, bearing the scars and calluses of someone well-versed in combat. His posture is military-straight, reflecting his current position of authority, while his facial features likely show the hardened expression of someone who has lived both outside and inside the law.', '* Aicantar - Direct superior whom he serves with professional dedication * Calcelmo - Respected authority figure whose work he is tasked with protecting * Guard Subordinates - Commands their respect through experience and firm leadership * Former Bandit Associates - Likely maintains distance from his past connections', 'Captain of the guard detail assigned to Calcelmo''s Tower in Markarth, responsible for the security of valuable Dwemer research and artifacts. His duties include leading patrols, coordinating with other guards, and responding to security threats within his jurisdiction.', '* Experienced warrior proficient with one-handed weapons and shield combat * Leadership abilities developed through both bandit and legitimate command roles * Tactical expertise in building security and patrol coordination * Knowledge of both criminal and guard operations from his varied background', 'Speaks with a gruff, authoritative tone befitting his position, using direct and precise language that emphasizes command and control. His manner of speech reflects both military discipline and street-smart awareness, carefully choosing words that maintain his authority while showing appropriate respect to his superiors.', '* Maintain his position of legitimate authority and continue distancing himself from his bandit past * Protect Calcelmo''s research and prove himself worthy of the trust placed in him * Further advance within Markarth''s security hierarchy through demonstrated competence and loyalty');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('captain_avidius', 'Captain Avidius is a distinguished Redguard officer in the Penitus Oculatus, serving as one of Emperor Titus Mede II''s most trusted protectors aboard The Katariah. As a veteran member of the Emperor''s elite guard, he demonstrates unwavering loyalty and exceptional dedication to his duties, embodying the disciplined professionalism that defines the Empire''s most prestigious security force.', 'redguard, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Rising through Imperial military ranks through dedication and martial prowess, Avidius earned his position in the Penitus Oculatus through years of exemplary service. His background as a Redguard warrior, combined with extensive training in Imperial military tactics, made him an ideal candidate for the Emperor''s personal security detail. After proving himself in numerous operations protecting Imperial interests, he was assigned to the Emperor''s flagship, The Katariah, as one of its senior security officers.', 'Avidius exhibits the stern professionalism and unwavering discipline expected of a high-ranking Penitus Oculatus officer. He maintains strict adherence to protocol and chain of command, showing little tolerance for breaches in security or procedural violations. Though capable of decisive action in crisis situations, he prefers methodical approaches to security challenges, always prioritizing the Emperor''s safety above all else.', 'A tall, muscular Redguard with sharp features and vigilant eyes that reflect years of military service. His physical bearing demonstrates the peak conditioning required of the Emperor''s elite guards, with a warrior''s practiced stance and precise movements. Despite his middle age, he maintains the fitness and alertness of a much younger soldier.', '* Emperor Titus Mede II - Direct superior and primary protection detail * Commander Maro - Superior officer in the Penitus Oculatus * Fellow Penitus Oculatus agents - Professional colleagues in service * Ship''s crew of The Katariah - Maintains professional oversight of their activities * Dark Brotherhood - Considered deadly enemies of the Empire', 'As a Captain in the Penitus Oculatus serving aboard The Katariah, Avidius oversees security protocols and coordinates protection details for the Emperor. His position requires him to manage both ship security and personal protection duties, making him responsible for the safety of both the vessel and its imperial passenger.', '* Master swordsman trained in both Redguard and Imperial combat techniques * Expert in close protection protocols and VIP security operations * Advanced knowledge of naval security procedures and maritime combat * Skilled tactician with expertise in defensive formations and security planning * Proficient in detection of assassins and counter-intelligence measures', 'Speaks with the formal, authoritative tone of a high-ranking Imperial officer, favoring precise military terminology and proper titles. His speech patterns reflect both his professional training and his role as a commander, maintaining a clear and commanding voice that expects immediate compliance.', '* Ensure the absolute safety and security of Emperor Titus Mede II * Maintain the highest standards of security aboard The Katariah * Advance the interests and protection capabilities of the Penitus Oculatus * Preserve the honor and integrity of his position as Captain');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('captain_hargar', 'Captain Hargar is a formidable Nord leader of the Blackblood Marauders, commanding his band of pirates from their hidden base in Broken Oar Grotto. A former prisoner who escaped from Castle Dour Dungeon, he has built a reputation as both a skilled warrior and cunning strategist, forming dangerous alliances with other criminal elements along Skyrim''s northern coast.', 'nord, thief, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised along Skyrim''s harsh northern coast, Hargar worked his way up through the ranks of various pirate crews before establishing his own band of marauders. His career in piracy was temporarily halted when he was captured and imprisoned in Castle Dour Dungeon, though he eventually orchestrated a daring escape. After regaining his freedom, he founded the Blackblood Marauders and established their base in Broken Oar Grotto, quickly becoming one of the most notorious pirates in the region.', 'Hargar is a ruthless yet principled leader who values loyalty above all else, showing fierce protection toward his crew while maintaining iron discipline. He possesses a pragmatic approach to leadership, willing to form strategic alliances with other criminal organizations when profitable, but never hesitating to eliminate threats to his operation. Despite his criminal nature, he adheres to a personal code of honor among thieves.', 'A weathered Nord of imposing stature, standing well over six feet tall with broad shoulders and powerful build typical of those who wield two-handed weapons. His face bears numerous scars from years of combat, with a thick beard and long hair bleached lighter by constant exposure to sea spray and sun.', '* Jaree-Ra - Criminal associate and co-conspirator in raiding operations * Deeja - Secondary contact through Jaree-Ra, trusted ally in current schemes * Blackblood Marauders - Loyal followers who respect his leadership and fighting prowess * Ahtar - Bitter enemy who seeks revenge for Hargar''s prison escape * East Empire Company - Primary target of raids and sworn enemies', 'Captain Hargar serves as both the leader of the Blackblood Marauders and the master of Broken Oar Grotto, coordinating all piracy operations along the northern coast of Skyrim. He personally oversees major raids and manages alliances with other criminal organizations, while maintaining direct command over his crew''s activities.', '* Master of two-handed combat, particularly skilled with greatswords and battleaxes * Experienced sailor and navigator of Skyrim''s treacherous northern waters * Tactical expertise in coordinating ship raids and coastal attacks * Natural leader with strong command presence and ability to inspire loyalty * Skilled escape artist, as demonstrated by his break from Castle Dour', 'Hargar speaks with a gruff, authoritative Nord accent, favoring direct commands and bold declarations that reflect his position of power. His vocabulary is that of a seasoned sailor, peppered with nautical terms and occasional crude expressions.', '* Expand the influence and territory of the Blackblood Marauders along Skyrim''s coast * Successfully execute the planned raid with Jaree-Ra and Deeja * Establish a stronger foothold in the regional criminal underworld * Acquire enough wealth to retire as a legendary pirate king');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('captain_lonely-gale', 'Captain Lonely-Gale is a retired Nord sea captain who made his fortune through maritime trade before settling in Windhelm. Now a respected elder of the city, he serves as an unofficial source of wisdom and information for its citizens, though he carries the weight of personal tragedy having lost his family years ago.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Rising from a common sailor to owning his own trading vessel, Lonely-Gale spent decades plying the waters around Skyrim, likely trading between major ports like Windhelm, Solitude, and Dawnstar. After losing his wife and family to unknown circumstances, he chose to retire in Windhelm, where his reputation and knowledge of trade earned him continued respect among the citizenry.', 'Despite his personal losses, Lonely-Gale maintains a dignified and patient demeanor, though he can be direct and occasionally gruff when annoyed. He shows a strong sense of civic duty and genuine concern for Windhelm''s wellbeing, while his years at sea have given him a practical, no-nonsense approach to life and a tendency to dismiss idle speculation.', 'A weathered Nord of advanced years, Lonely-Gale bears the hardy physique of a longtime sailor, with calloused hands and sun-weathered skin. His bearing remains straight and proud despite his age, reflecting his years of command at sea.', '* Viola Giordano - Persistent would-be suitor whose advances he actively avoids * Brunwulf Free-Winter - Respected peer and potential employer (intended future steward) * Windhelm Citizens - Generally respected by the community as a source of wisdom * Market Vendors - Regular daily interactions during his morning shopping routine * Lost Family - Deceased wife and family members whose memory he still carries', 'Though officially retired, Lonely-Gale serves as an unofficial advisor and information source for Windhelm''s citizens and visitors. His extensive knowledge of trade and city affairs makes him a valuable source of insight for both common folk and nobility.', '* Experienced navigator and seafarer * Skilled trader and negotiator from years of maritime commerce * Proficient swordsman, maintaining combat readiness despite retirement * Extensive knowledge of Windhelm''s politics, commerce, and social dynamics * Leadership abilities developed through years as a ship''s captain', 'Speaks with the measured tone of a seasoned commander, frequently employing nautical metaphors and expressions from his sailing days. His manner is direct but courteous, reflecting both his military background and years of diplomatic trading interactions.', '* Maintain his dignity and independence in retirement despite unwanted romantic attention * Preserve and share his knowledge of Windhelm''s affairs with those who seek his counsel * Keep watch over the city''s wellbeing, particularly during troubled times * Find purpose in his twilight years despite the loss of his family');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('captain_valmir', 'Captain Valmir is a cunning Thalmor agent who poses as either an Imperial or Stormcloak officer at Forelhost, manipulating others to retrieve powerful artifacts. His deceptive operation reveals the sophisticated intelligence gathering methods of the Thalmor and their ongoing efforts to acquire ancient Nordic artifacts of power.', 'highelf, warrior, rift, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Trained as a Thalmor operative, Valmir was selected for covert operations in Skyrim due to his talent for deception and knowledge of Nordic history. He was assigned to recover powerful artifacts from ancient Nordic ruins, specifically targeting items connected to the Dragon Cult that could benefit the Aldmeri Dominion''s interests.', 'Valmir is calculating, manipulative, and inherently cowardly, preferring to let others take risks while he maintains his cover. He displays remarkable adaptability in his role-playing abilities, seamlessly switching between Imperial and Stormcloak personalities depending on his target. Despite his confident facade, he becomes notably anxious when questioned too deeply about his supposed military credentials.', 'As a High Elf, Valmir stands tall with the characteristic golden skin and high cheekbones of his race. His face bears subtle stress lines from years of maintaining false identities, and his posture attempts to mimic military bearing but occasionally betrays his civilian nature.', '* Thalmor High Command - His direct superiors who assigned him this covert mission * Local Soldiers - Maintains cautious distance to avoid detection of his false identity * Dragon Cult Research Team - Likely connects with other Thalmor agents studying ancient Nordic powers * Rahgot (deceased Dragon Priest) - Target of his mission to acquire powerful artifacts', 'Valmir operates as a covert Thalmor intelligence agent, specializing in artifact retrieval operations. His cover identity as a military officer allows him to manipulate both Imperial and Stormcloak sympathizers into doing the dangerous work of exploring ruins while he maintains his position of relative safety.', '* Expert in deception and maintaining false identities * Knowledgeable about Nordic history and the Dragon Cult * Basic combat training with both Imperial and Stormcloak fighting styles * Competent in destruction magic, particularly flame spells * Skilled in restoration magic for self-preservation', 'Valmir adopts a formal military manner of speech, using appropriate terminology and ranks, though his dialogue becomes hesitant and evasive when challenged about his credentials. He maintains different accents and mannerisms depending on whether he''s posing as an Imperial or Stormcloak officer.', '* Acquire powerful artifacts from Nordic ruins for the Thalmor * Maintain his cover identity while gathering intelligence on both civil war factions * Advance his position within the Thalmor hierarchy through successful missions * Avoid direct combat or personal risk while achieving his objectives');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('captain_veleth', 'Captain Modyn Veleth is a battle-hardened Dark Elf warrior who serves as the commanding officer of the Redoran Guard in Raven Rock, Solstheim. A dedicated and vigilant protector, he maintains order in the troubled settlement while serving as the personal guardian of Councilor Morvayn, balancing his stern military discipline with a deep concern for the welfare of both his men and the town''s citizens.', 'darkelf, guard, noble, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_modyn', '', 'Originally commanding over a hundred troops in Morrowind, Veleth''s fortunes changed when his homeland was devastated by the Red Mountain''s eruption. He was later appointed as Captain of the Redoran Guard in Raven Rock, specially chosen to protect Councilor Morvayn due to his exceptional military record and unwavering loyalty to House Redoran.', 'Veleth exhibits a stern, no-nonsense demeanor that masks a deeply protective nature toward those under his command and the citizens he serves. While he can be brusque and sometimes harsh in his methods, he possesses a strong sense of duty and honor, showing compassion when circumstances warrant it. His military background has instilled in him a preference for direct action and clear solutions over political maneuvering.', 'A weathered Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, bearing the hardened physique of a career soldier. His face shows the marks of years of combat experience and exposure to the harsh ash-laden winds of Solstheim, with a rigid posture that reflects his military bearing.', '* Dreyla Alor - Secret lover whom he meets regularly at the Retching Netch * Councilor Morvayn - Superior and primary protectee, whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Redoran Guard Members - Subordinates he trains and leads with stern but fair leadership * Second Councilor Arano - Close working relationship as fellow protector of Councilor Morvayn * Ash Spawn - Persistent enemies threatening Raven Rock''s security', 'As Captain of the Redoran Guard, Veleth oversees all security operations in Raven Rock, including guard assignments, patrol schedules, and threat assessment. He serves as both the town''s chief law enforcement officer and military commander, with additional duties as personal security coordinator for Councilor Morvayn.', '* Expert in combat leadership and tactical planning * Highly skilled in heavy armor combat and battlefield coordination * Proficient with two-handed weapons, particularly the elven battleaxe * Advanced knowledge of bonemold armor maintenance and military logistics * Experienced in ash spawn combat tactics and town defense strategies', 'Speaks with a gruff, authoritative tone befitting his military background, often using direct and unembellished language. His speech patterns reflect his Dunmer heritage and military training, frequently emphasizing duty, honor, and the need for vigilance.', '* Maintain the security and prosperity of Raven Rock against both internal and external threats * Ensure the continued safety of Councilor Morvayn and uphold House Redoran''s interests * Train and maintain an elite fighting force capable of defending against ash spawn and other dangers * Restore Raven Rock to its former glory as a thriving colonial settlement');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('captain_wayfinder', 'Leif Wayfinder is a young, inexperienced Nord captain who inherited the Sea Squall from his mother, struggling to prove himself worthy of command despite his limited maritime expertise. Operating from Dawnstar''s harbor, he leads with an unusually relaxed management style while working to earn his crew''s respect and establish legitimate trading operations.', 'nord, thief, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born to a seasoned ship captain mother who ran a tight ship and successful trading operation, Leif grew up learning navigation and starcharting aboard the Sea Squall. Following his mother''s unexpected death, he inherited the vessel and its crew despite having minimal leadership experience, forcing him to quickly adapt to the role of captain while maintaining existing trade relationships.', 'Unlike traditional Nordic sea captains, Wayfinder favors a more casual and friendly approach to leadership, believing that happy sailors make better workers. Though somewhat insecure about his capabilities, he maintains an optimistic attitude and shows determination to prove his worth, while being honest about his shortcomings and willing to seek help when needed.', 'A young Nord in his mid-twenties with the characteristic tall, sturdy build of his race, though lacking the weathered features typical of seasoned sailors. His skin remains relatively fair from spending most of his time in Dawnstar''s cold climate, and his bearing, while attempting to project authority, betrays his youth and inexperience.', '* Mother (Deceased) - Former captain of the Sea Squall and his primary influence in seafaring * Guthrum - Crew member who seems accepting of his leadership style * Ravam Verethi - Bitter crew member who questions his authority * College of Winterhold - Business contact for trading valuable alchemical ingredients', 'Captain of the merchant vessel Sea Squall, primarily handling local trading operations along Skyrim''s northern coast. His duties include managing crew, maintaining trade relationships, and overseeing cargo shipments, though the ship currently remains docked in Dawnstar while he builds his reputation.', '* Proficient in navigation and star-charting * Basic swordsmanship for self-defense * Fundamental knowledge of trading and merchant operations * Developing leadership abilities * Working understanding of shipping logistics and cargo management', 'Speaks with a mix of attempted authority and youthful enthusiasm, often qualifying his statements with honest admissions about his inexperience. His vocabulary combines maritime terminology with common Nordic speech patterns, though he sometimes stumbles when trying to sound more captain-like.', '* Prove himself as a worthy successor to his mother''s legacy * Earn the genuine respect of his crew members * Establish profitable trade routes and business relationships * Develop into a competent and respected ship captain * Restore the Sea Squall''s reputation as a reliable merchant vessel');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('carlotta_valentia', 'Carlotta Valentia is a resilient Imperial merchant who has carved out a successful business selling produce in Whiterun''s marketplace while raising her daughter as a single mother. She represents the determined spirit of independent businesswomen in Skyrim, dealing with both the challenges of commerce and unwanted romantic attention from local men.', 'imperial, merchant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Carlotta moved to Whiterun seeking better opportunities for herself and her daughter. The circumstances of her daughter''s father are unknown, though her strong aversion to romantic entanglements suggests possible past trauma or disappointment. She has built her merchant business through a partnership with Severio Pelagia, who supplies most of her produce.', 'Carlotta is fiercely independent and protective of her autonomy, particularly when it comes to romantic advances from men. She exhibits both strength and kindness, shown through her firm handling of unwanted suitors and her occasional charity toward local beggars. Despite the hardships of single motherhood, she maintains a professional demeanor and strong work ethic.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with the weathered hands of someone who works with produce daily, yet maintains an appearance attractive enough to draw frequent male attention. She has the sturdy build of someone who regularly carries heavy merchandise and stands for long hours.', '* Mila Valentia - Her beloved daughter whom she''s determined to raise properly without male interference * Mikael - Unwanted suitor and source of harassment at the Bannered Mare * Severio Pelagia - Business partner who supplies her produce * Brenuin - Local beggar she occasionally helps with food * Various Whiterun men - Both married and single who have proposed to her', 'Carlotta owns and operates a produce stand in Whiterun''s marketplace, working long hours to maintain her business. She manages all aspects of her operation, from procurement through Severio Pelagia''s farm to daily sales and customer relations.', '* Expert haggling and mercantile abilities * Produce quality assessment and selection * Basic self-defense with a dagger * Household management and child-rearing * Food preservation and storage techniques', 'She speaks directly and professionally to customers, but can be sharp-tongued when dealing with unwanted advances. Her Imperial accent carries traces of her Cyrodilic origins, though tempered by years in Skyrim.', '* Provide a stable and comfortable life for her daughter Mila * Maintain her independence and successful business without relying on a man * Establish herself as one of Whiterun''s most respected merchants * Keep unwanted suitors, particularly Mikael, at bay');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cedran', 'Cedran is a pragmatic Breton hostler who manages the Markarth Stables, serving as one of the city''s primary horse traders and stable masters. His position at the outskirts of Markarth gives him unique insight into both the city''s political climate and the ongoing tensions between Nords, Bretons, and Forsworn in the Reach.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Cedran likely grew up during the tumultuous period of Forsworn uprising and subsequent Nord reconquest of Markarth. Having witnessed the Markarth Incident firsthand, he chose a neutral path focusing on business rather than politics, eventually establishing himself as the stable master at Markarth''s main stables.', 'Cedran exhibits a practical, business-minded approach to life, preferring to stay neutral in political conflicts while maintaining enough awareness to survive in the Reach''s complicated political landscape. He shows genuine care for his horses and maintains a professional relationship with his workers, demonstrating both leadership and pragmatism in his daily operations.', 'A middle-aged Breton male with the weathered features typical of someone who works outdoors. His build is sturdy and practical, developed from years of physical labor with horses and stable maintenance.', '* Banning - Trusted assistant and colleague at the stables * Jarl Igmund/Thongvor Silver-Blood - Professional relationship as a business owner under their rule * Local merchants - Business connections for stable supplies and trade * Forsworn - Maintains cautious distance while acknowledging shared heritage', 'As the hostler of Markarth Stables, Cedran manages all aspects of the business including horse sales, care, and maintenance. He oversees stable operations, handles customer relations, and ensures the facility''s financial success while maintaining its reputation as a reliable source for horses in the Reach.', '* Expert horse trainer and caretaker * Experienced business manager and trader * Knowledgeable about local geography and safe travel routes * Basic combat abilities for self-defense with an iron dagger * Understanding of Reach politics and history', 'Speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of a businessman, often offering practical advice about horses and travel. His dialogue reflects his neutral stance on politics while still showing his deep knowledge of local affairs.', '* Maintain a successful and reputable stable business in Markarth * Preserve his neutrality in the region''s political conflicts while ensuring his business''s survival * Expand his horse trading operation when possible while maintaining quality standards');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('celann', 'Celann is a seasoned Breton vampire hunter and former Vigilant of Stendarr who became one of the founding members of the Dawnguard. His experience, dedication, and slightly more moderate approach compared to Isran make him a valuable asset to the vampire-hunting organization while serving as a stabilizing influence within the fort.', 'breton, warrior, rift, dawnguard, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally trained as a Vigilant of Stendarr, Celann left the organization alongside Isran due to frustrations with their methods and effectiveness. After parting ways with Isran for a time due to disagreements over extreme tactics, he later rejoined his former colleague as one of the first recruits when the Dawnguard was reformed, believing the vampire threat required a more focused and militant response than the Vigilants could provide.', 'Celann is dutiful and dedicated to the Dawnguard''s mission, but maintains a more measured approach than his leader Isran. While firm in his convictions about destroying vampires, he shows greater patience with recruits and allies, demonstrating pragmatism tempered by experience. His disagreement with Isran''s harshest methods suggests a moral compass that seeks balance between effectiveness and ethical constraints.', 'As a Breton, Celann has the characteristic medium build and average height of his race. Years of combat training and vampire hunting have kept him physically fit and battle-ready. His face likely bears the weathered look of someone who spends considerable time on watch and patrol duties.', '* Isran - Former Vigilant colleague and current leader, relationship marked by respect despite past disagreements * Durak - Fellow senior Dawnguard member and combat ally * Agmaer - Mentor figure to new recruits like him * Vigilants of Stendarr - Former associates, maintains cautious respect despite leaving their ranks', 'Celann serves as a senior member of the Dawnguard, combining roles as fortress defender, vampire hunter, and mentor to new recruits. His position includes regular patrol duties, combat training, and participating in operations against vampire threats across Skyrim.', '* Expert in vampire hunting tactics and detection * Skilled with one-handed weapons, particularly war axes * Proficient in light armor combat techniques * Knowledgeable in Restoration magic, especially sun-based spells * Experienced fortress defender and patrol specialist', 'Celann speaks with the measured tone of an experienced warrior, direct but less harsh than Isran. His speech reflects his military background while maintaining an approachable demeanor that makes him effective at dealing with new recruits.', '* Protect Skyrim from the growing vampire menace * Help build the Dawnguard into an effective vampire-hunting force * Maintain vigilance against vampire infiltration of society * Prove that the Dawnguard''s methods can be both effective and measured');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('challenger', 'The Challenger is a wandering Breton wizard who roams Skyrim seeking magical duels to prove his superiority in the arcane arts. Driven by an obsessive need to validate his magical prowess, he confronts other spellcasters in ritualistic magical combat, adhering strictly to his personal code of magical honor.', 'breton, mage, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Trained at a young age in the magical arts, likely at the College of Winterhold or another prestigious magical institution, the Challenger developed an intense competitive streak and became fixated on proving himself the superior mage. After leaving formal magical education, he began wandering Skyrim, challenging other mages to duels as a way to build his reputation and satisfy his need for magical combat.', 'Arrogant and confrontational, the Challenger possesses an unwavering belief in the superiority of magical combat over physical warfare. He follows a strict personal code regarding magical duels, becoming agitated when others don''t adhere to his self-imposed rules. His obsession with magical prowess borders on fanaticism, leading him to challenge even strangers to potentially deadly combat.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with the typical slight build common to his race. His hands show the telltale signs of frequent spellcasting - slight magical burns and a faint arcane glow. His face bears the focused intensity of someone who has dedicated their life to mastering the magical arts.', '* College of Winterhold - Likely former student, though possibly expelled for aggressive behavior * Local Guards - Tense relationship due to his provocative dueling habits * Court Wizards - Views them as potential rivals and duel targets * Fellow Wandering Mages - Sees them as competition to be challenged', 'The Challenger is a self-styled magical duelist who makes his living through wandering Skyrim seeking worthy opponents. He likely sustains himself through a combination of looting defeated opponents and performing magical services for hire between duels.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Proficient in Restoration magic for self-healing during duels * Skilled in Alteration magic for magical protection * Advanced knowledge of magical theory and dueling etiquette * Competent alchemist, creating combat-enhancing potions', 'Speaks with a haughty, challenging tone that reflects his superiority complex regarding magical ability. Uses formal language with frequent references to magic and dueling terminology, often speaking in proclamations rather than casual conversation.', '* Prove himself as the supreme magical duelist in Skyrim * Perfect his mastery of destructive magic * Build a reputation that will draw more powerful mages to challenge * Establish a formal circuit of magical dueling across the province');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('champion_of_boethiah', 'A former champion of the Daedric Prince Boethiah who turned his back on a life of violence and treachery to pursue the noble craft of armorsmithing. Now residing in Knifepoint Ridge, this Dark Elf lives under the constant shadow of Boethiah''s wrath while striving to create rather than destroy, representing a rare example of someone who successfully broke free from a Daedric Prince''s influence.', 'darkelf, warrior, eastmarch, daedric', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, he was drawn to Boethiah''s sphere of deceit and lawlessness in his youth, eventually rising to become her champion through acts of cunning and bloodshed. After years of serving the Daedric Prince''s whims, he experienced a profound moral awakening that led him to reject his role, despite knowing the grave consequences of such defiance. He fled to Skyrim and settled in Knifepoint Ridge, where he redirected his intimate knowledge of armor from warfare to craftsmanship.', 'Proud and defiant, he maintains unwavering conviction in his choice to abandon Boethiah despite the constant threat to his life. While he carries the weight of his past deeds, he channels his guilt into a determined focus on creating protective armor that might save lives rather than take them. His experiences have left him with a philosophical outlook on mortality and redemption, though he harbors no illusions about eventually facing Boethiah''s vengeance.', 'A weathered Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and ashen skin of his race, bearing numerous scars from his violent past as Boethiah''s champion. His muscular frame and calloused hands reflect both his warrior background and his current work as a smith, while his face shows the signs of someone who has lived through considerable hardship.', '* Boethiah - Former patron turned deadly enemy who seeks his death * Local merchants - Cautious business relationships for trading materials and finished goods * Fellow craftsmen - Respected but distant professional connections * Wandering adventurers - Occasional customers who seek his expertise in armor crafting', 'Master armorsmith operating independently from Knifepoint Ridge, specializing in protective gear that emphasizes preservation of life rather than offensive capabilities. He maintains a modest workshop where he creates and sells his craft while keeping a low profile to avoid drawing attention from Boethiah''s cultists.', '* Master-level armorer with extensive knowledge of various crafting techniques * Exceptional combat abilities gained from years as Boethiah''s champion * Expert in Dunmer fighting styles and traditional armor design * Intimate knowledge of Daedric artifacts and enchantments * Skilled strategist and tactician from years of warfare', 'He speaks with the formal, measured tones common to educated Dunmer, often incorporating philosophical observations about life, death, and redemption into his conversations. His voice carries both wisdom and weariness, reflecting his complex past and current situation.', '* Create armor that will protect and preserve life rather than enable bloodshed * Find a way to permanently break free from Boethiah''s influence * Pass on his knowledge of armorcrafting to worthy apprentices * Establish a legacy of creation that outweighs his past destruction');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('chief_burguk', 'Chief Burguk is the proud and formidable leader of Dushnikh Yal, an Orc stronghold near Markarth, where he maintains traditional Orcish customs and serves as a master trainer in One-handed combat. He exemplifies Orcish strength and leadership through his management of three wives and the stronghold''s affairs, while upholding the warrior culture of his people.', 'orc, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in the tradition of Malacath, Burguk proved himself worthy of leadership through combat and strength, eventually becoming chief of Dushnikh Yal. He established his position by taking three wives according to Orcish custom and maintaining the stronghold''s independence and prosperity in the harsh lands of the Reach.', 'Burguk is boastful and proud, quick to assert his dominance through challenges and displays of strength. Despite his gruff exterior, he shows wisdom in managing tribal politics and maintaining balance among his wives, though his favoritism toward Shel creates occasional tension. He deeply respects Orcish traditions and frequently seeks counsel from his mother Murbul regarding Malacath''s favor.', 'A powerful and imposing Orc male with the characteristic green skin and tusks of his race. His muscular build and battle-hardened physique reflect years of combat training and leadership. His bearing is proud and commanding, befitting his position as tribal chief.', '* Shel - His favorite wife, whom he openly favors and protects from manual labor * Gharol - His forge-wife, responsible for smithing duties * Arob - His hunt-wife, who provides food for the stronghold * Murbul - His mother and tribal wise woman, whom he consults for spiritual guidance * Nagrub - His son, who serves the stronghold * Ghorbash the Iron Hand - His brother, a warrior of the stronghold', 'Chief of Dushnikh Yal, where he oversees all aspects of stronghold life and serves as its primary defender and leader. He also acts as a master trainer in One-handed combat, sharing his expertise with those who prove worthy.', '* Master-level expertise in One-handed weapon combat * Advanced heavy armor proficiency * Leadership and tribal management capabilities * Strategic decision-making and conflict resolution * Traditional Orcish combat techniques', 'Speaks in a gruff, authoritative manner with frequent boasts about his strength and prowess. Uses direct, commanding language that emphasizes his position as chief and his personal power.', '* Maintain the strength and prosperity of Dushnikh Yal * Uphold traditional Orcish ways and Malacath''s teachings * Ensure his stronghold remains respected among other Orc settlements * Train worthy warriors in the art of One-handed combat * Preserve the balance of power among his wives while maintaining his authority');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('chief_larak', 'Chief Larak is the proud and traditionalist leader of the Mor Khazgur Orc stronghold, serving as both its chieftain and master shield-bearer. A former Legion veteran turned tribal leader, he upholds the ancient Orcish ways with unwavering dedication while maintaining his stronghold''s security and prosperity through strict adherence to the Code of Malacath.', 'orc, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born to the wise-woman Sharamph in Mor Khazgur, Larak earned his position as chief by defeating his father in ritual combat, as per Orcish tradition. His time serving in the Imperial Legion provided him with valuable combat experience and knowledge of foreign military techniques, which he later incorporated into his leadership style while maintaining traditional Orcish values.', 'Larak embodies the stern, honor-bound nature typical of Orc chieftains, displaying unwavering commitment to ancient traditions and tribal law. He maintains a gruff, authoritative demeanor befitting his station, yet shows moments of pride and tenderness when discussing his forge-wife''s craftsmanship or interacting with family members. His leadership style balances strict adherence to the Code of Malacath with practical wisdom gained from his Legion experience.', 'A towering Orsimer male with the characteristic muscular build and tusks of his race, bearing numerous battle scars that testify to his combat experience. His powerful physique reflects both his warrior lifestyle and the physical demands of chieftain combat trials, while his bearing conveys the natural authority of a tribal leader.', '* Sharamph - Mother and stronghold''s wise-woman, whom he deeply respects * Shuftharz - Forge-wife, whose smithing skills he openly admires * Borgakh the Steel Heart - Daughter and warrior * Olur - Son who assists in the forge * Bagrak - Brother and fellow stronghold member * Imperial Legion - Former service connection, maintaining neutral relations', 'As chieftain of Mor Khazgur, Larak serves as the stronghold''s primary leader, military commander, and judicial authority. He maintains order through enforcement of traditional laws, oversees the stronghold''s defense, and makes all major decisions affecting the community while serving as a master trainer in shield combat techniques.', '* Master-level expertise in shield combat and blocking techniques * Veteran warrior with extensive military training from Imperial Legion service * Skilled leader and administrator of tribal law and customs * Proficient in traditional Orcish combat styles * Working knowledge of Imperial military tactics and discipline', 'Larak speaks with a deep, commanding voice that reflects his position of authority, using direct and formal language that emphasizes tradition and honor. His dialogue often references his position as chief and the importance of Orcish customs, maintaining a serious, no-nonsense tone.', '* Maintain the strength and prosperity of Mor Khazgur through strict adherence to traditional ways * Pass on his shield-bearing expertise to worthy warriors * Prepare his stronghold for the day his successor will eventually challenge him * Preserve the balance between traditional Orcish ways and beneficial outside influences');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('chief_mauhulakh', 'Chief Mauhulakh is the troubled leader of Narzulbur, an Orc stronghold known for its valuable ebony mine. He is a figure of both authority and tragedy, marked by a mysterious curse that has claimed the lives of all his wives, leaving him to rely on his aunts while searching for a mate worthy of surviving the divine judgment that seems to plague him.', 'orc, warrior, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into the nobility of Narzulbur, Mauhulakh inherited leadership of the stronghold and its lucrative Gloombound Mine. His reign has been marked by both prosperity from the ebony trade and personal tragedy, having lost multiple wives to mysterious deaths, particularly during childbirth. This pattern of loss has led him to believe he is cursed by the gods, though he maintains his duties as chieftain while seeking spiritual guidance from his aunts.', 'Mauhulakh is a contemplative and melancholic leader who maintains dignity despite his personal struggles. While he carries the weight of his perceived curse heavily, he remains surprisingly open and friendly to outsiders, demonstrating a progressive attitude unusual for an Orc chieftain. His relationship with his aunts reveals a somewhat dependent nature, unusual for an Orc leader, as he often seeks their counsel and approval.', 'As an Orc chieftain, Mauhulakh possesses the characteristic robust build and imposing stature of his race, with the distinctive tusks and green-tinted skin. His face likely bears the traditional ritual scars of an Orc leader, marking his status and achievements within the stronghold.', '* Dushnamub - His son, who observes the unusual dynamic between his father and aunts * Urog - His daughter, who lives in the stronghold * Bolar - His aunt who serves as spiritual advisor and caretaker * Yatul - His second aunt who helps care for him * Galka - One of his deceased wives (mentioned specifically) * Mine Workers - Outsourced laborers from other tribes, indicating his pragmatic leadership', 'As Chieftain of Narzulbur, Mauhulakh oversees all aspects of the stronghold''s operations, particularly the valuable Gloombound Mine. He manages trade relations, makes diplomatic decisions, and maintains the stronghold''s security while ensuring the profitable extraction of ebony ore.', '* Capable warrior skilled enough to maintain his position as chieftain * Administrative expertise in managing mining operations * Diplomatic ability in dealing with outsiders and trade negotiations * Leadership capabilities in maintaining stronghold cohesion despite personal struggles', 'Mauhulakh speaks with formal authority tempered by introspective melancholy, often expressing his thoughts on spiritual matters and his curse. His dialogue reveals both his position of power and his personal vulnerability, creating a unique blend of strength and uncertainty.', '* Find a wife who can survive the perceived curse and bear him more children * Maintain the prosperity and stability of Narzulbur through successful mining operations * Understand and potentially break the curse that has claimed his previous wives * Prove himself worthy of the gods'' favor and restore his full strength as a traditional Orc chieftain');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('chief_yamarz', 'Chief Yamarz is a deeply flawed Orc chieftain whose weakness and cowardice have brought shame to the stronghold of Largashbur. As the leader of a cursed tribe, he represents the antithesis of traditional Orcish values, embodying corruption and decline rather than the strength and honor typically associated with Orc chiefs.', 'orc, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Yamarz rose to position of chief through unknown means, though his leadership has been marked by failure and dishonor. Under his weak rule, the stronghold fell into decline and eventually became cursed by Malacath himself, with giants repeatedly attacking and defiling their sacred shrine. His inability to defend his people and sacred sites suggests he may have gained his position through deceit rather than traditional combat.', 'Unlike typical Orc chiefs who embody strength and directness, Yamarz is cowardly, manipulative, and prone to shifting blame onto others. He displays a remarkable aversion to combat for an Orc chief and attempts to manipulate others into fighting his battles. His demeanor is consistently unpleasant, showing both arrogance towards his tribe members and fear of confronting actual threats.', 'Yamarz possesses the typical robust build of an Orc male, though his posture often betrays uncertainty rather than confidence. His tusks and facial features are less prominent than those of many Orc males, giving him a somewhat softer appearance that matches his less warrior-like nature.', '* Atub - Wise woman of his tribe who seeks to help lift the curse, though he often dismisses her counsel * Malacath - Daedric Prince who has cursed his tribe due to his weak leadership * Tribe Members - Increasingly disappointed and distrustful of his leadership * Giants - Enemies who have taken over Malacath''s shrine and repeatedly attack the stronghold', 'Chief of Largashbur, though his leadership is largely ineffective. As chief, he is supposed to protect his people and maintain the stronghold''s strength, but has failed in these fundamental duties.', '* Basic proficiency with traditional Orcish weapons, though rarely demonstrated * Some capability in wearing and maintaining heavy armor * Leadership position suggests some administrative abilities, though poorly executed * Manipulation and deception, unusual skills for an Orc chief', 'Yamarz speaks with a mix of aggression and defensiveness, often trying to maintain his authority through harsh words rather than actions. His speech patterns reveal his cowardly nature, frequently deflecting responsibility and complaining about his circumstances.', '* Maintain his position as chief despite his obvious failings * Avoid direct combat while appearing strong to his tribe * Find ways to delegate dangerous tasks to others * Survive the curse placed upon his stronghold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('christer', 'Christer is a desperate Nord husband searching for his missing wife Fjola at the Mistwatch bandit stronghold. His deep love and devotion drive him to venture far beyond his comfort zone, though his lack of combat prowess forces him to seek help from others while hiding in a supply closet.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally a simple farmer living a peaceful life with his beloved wife Fjola, Christer''s world was shattered when she disappeared during what should have been routine errands. After months of searching and following rumors of bandit ransoms, he tracked her possible location to Mistwatch, where he managed to sneak past the outer guards but could proceed no further due to his limited combat abilities.', 'Christer is a deeply devoted and emotionally fragile individual, whose entire world revolves around finding his missing wife. He displays signs of anxiety and desperation, coupled with a notable lack of self-confidence in his abilities. Despite his cowardice in combat situations, he shows remarkable determination in his search, having traveled far from his farm and risked entering a bandit stronghold.', 'A typical Nord male with the sturdy build common to his race, though likely somewhat weathered from months of searching and worry. His physical appearance likely shows signs of stress and fatigue, with dark circles under his eyes and a generally unkempt appearance from living in a supply closet.', '* Fjola - His beloved wife who mysteriously disappeared * Local Farmers - Former neighbors and community members he left behind to search for Fjola * Bandits of Mistwatch - Perceived enemies whom he believes are holding his wife captive * The Last Dragonborn - Potential ally in his quest to find Fjola', 'Originally a farmer by trade, Christer has abandoned his agricultural life to become a full-time searcher for his missing wife. His current ''occupation'' consists solely of trying to locate Fjola, having seemingly left behind all other responsibilities.', '* Basic farming and agricultural knowledge * Limited stealth capabilities, enough to sneak past outer guards * Survival skills sufficient to maintain himself during his search * No combat abilities or warrior training', 'Christer speaks in a frantic, emotional manner with frequent pleading tones and desperate inflections. His dialogue is often punctuated by worried exclamations and anxious requests for help.', '* Find and rescue his wife Fjola from her perceived captivity * Return to his peaceful farming life with his beloved wife * Escape from Mistwatch alive, either with Fjola or with confirmation of her fate');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cicero', 'Cicero is the eccentric and mentally unstable Keeper of the Night Mother for the Dark Brotherhood, devoted wholly to maintaining ancient traditions and serving the unholy matron of his order. His outwardly foolish jester''s persona masks a dangerous and skilled assassin who takes his sacred duties with unwavering, though maniacal, dedication.', 'imperial, thief, skyrimall, darkbrotherhood, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_cicero', '', 'Originally a skilled assassin of the Cheydinhal Sanctuary in Cyrodiil, Cicero witnessed the Dark Brotherhood''s decline firsthand and eventually became the Keeper of the Night Mother in 4E 188. His years of isolation while protecting and maintaining the Night Mother''s corpse, combined with the Brotherhood''s deterioration and abandonment of the old ways, gradually eroded his sanity. His final assassination of a jester inspired his current persona.', 'Cicero is defined by his absolute devotion to the Night Mother and the ancient traditions of the Dark Brotherhood, manifesting in obsessive-compulsive behaviors regarding his Keeper duties. His apparent madness masks a calculating mind, and his jovial exterior can quickly give way to murderous rage when the Night Mother or old ways are disrespected. Despite his insanity, he maintains an unwavering loyalty to whoever is proven to be the true Listener.', 'A slight but wiry Imperial man with reddish-brown hair and sharp features that often twist into exaggerated expressions. His face shows signs of aging and stress, with pronounced laugh lines and dark circles under his eyes. His body is lean and agile, built for swift, deadly movement rather than brute strength.', '* Night Mother - Sacred matron whom he serves with fanatical devotion * Astrid - Antagonistic relationship due to her rejection of traditional Dark Brotherhood values * Dark Brotherhood members - Mixed relations, viewed with suspicion by most * The Listener (potentially player) - Absolute loyalty once proven as true Listener * Loreius - Frustrated relationship with farmer who refuses to help fix his wagon', 'As Keeper of the Night Mother, Cicero is responsible for maintaining and protecting the Night Mother''s corpse, including regular oils, preservatives, and sacred rituals. This holy position within the Dark Brotherhood places him among the highest ranking members, though his authority is often undermined by more progressive factions within the organization.', '* Expert in blade combat, particularly with daggers and short blades * Masterful assassin trained in stealth and silent killing * Knowledgeable in corpse preservation and maintenance * Skilled performer and deceiver, using his jester persona effectively * Expert in Dark Brotherhood history, rituals, and traditions', 'Speaks in an exaggerated, sing-song voice, often referring to himself in the third person and punctuating sentences with maniacal laughter. Frequently uses rhymes, riddles, and dark humor in his speech, mixing childlike playfulness with disturbing undertones.', '* Protect and serve the Night Mother with absolute dedication * Find the true Listener to restore the Dark Brotherhood''s traditional hierarchy * Return the Dark Brotherhood to its ancient ways and traditions * Eliminate those who would desecrate or disrespect the old ways');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cindiri_arano', 'Cindiri Arano is a sophisticated Dark Elf noblewoman and wife of Raven Rock''s Second Councilor, struggling with the isolation of Solstheim and longing for her homeland. Despite her privileged position in Raven Rock''s society, she harbors deep concerns for her husband''s safety and yearns to return to the grandeur of Blacklight.', 'darkelf, noble, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Originally from the grand city of Blacklight, Cindiri lived through the destruction of Vvardenfell and eventually settled in Raven Rock with her husband Adril. She has not seen her beloved hometown in fifty years, having followed her husband in his political duties to serve Councilor Morvayn, though the move was clearly not her preference.', 'Cindiri is refined and proud, carrying herself with the dignity befitting her social status while harboring deep-seated anxieties about her husband''s dangerous position. She is notably nostalgic for her homeland and somewhat resentful of their prolonged stay in Raven Rock, though she maintains a stoic public facade. Her concern for her husband''s safety reveals a deeply loving and protective nature beneath her formal exterior.', 'As a Dark Elf of noble bearing, Cindiri has the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of her race, with features that suggest both age and refinement. Her posture and movements reflect her upper-class upbringing, and she maintains a well-groomed appearance despite Raven Rock''s harsh conditions.', '* Adril Arano - Beloved husband whose safety she constantly worries about * Councilor Morvayn - Superior to her husband and frequent social contact * Raven Rock Elite - Maintains formal social connections with other prominent citizens * Blacklight Contacts - Distant but maintained connections to her homeland', 'As the wife of the Second Councilor, Cindiri maintains a prominent social position in Raven Rock''s upper class. Her duties include attending formal functions at Morvayn Manor and maintaining the social connections necessary for her husband''s political position.', '* Educated in proper etiquette and noble customs of Great House Redoran * Competent in household management and social organization * Basic self-defense training with an elven dagger * Knowledge of Dunmer history and politics', 'Cindiri speaks with refined diction and formal mannerisms typical of Dunmer nobility, often employing sophisticated vocabulary and proper etiquette. Her tone carries subtle hints of both pride and melancholy, reflecting her current situation in Raven Rock.', '* Convince her husband to return to Blacklight and leave his dangerous position * Maintain her family''s social status and connections in Raven Rock * Protect her husband from potential threats to his safety * Recover and preserve important family heirlooms');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('coldhearted_gravedigger', 'The Coldhearted Gravedigger is a solemn Nord warrior who maintains Windhelm''s Hall of the Dead with a grim dedication born from years of tending to the deceased. Her weary demeanor and morbid outlook reflect the psychological toll of her isolated profession, making her a mysterious figure who walks the line between the worlds of the living and the dead.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm''s harsh climate, she took up the role of gravedigger after losing her family during a particularly harsh winter. Her intimate familiarity with death from an early age led her to find purpose in providing dignity to the deceased, eventually becoming the primary caretaker of Windhelm''s Hall of the Dead. The constant exposure to death and isolation has gradually worn away at her spirit, leading to her current state of perpetual exhaustion and melancholy.', 'The Gravedigger maintains a stoic and detached demeanor, speaking frankly about death and showing little interest in the affairs of the living. Years of solitary work have left her with a deeply nihilistic worldview, often expressing her own longing for eternal rest. Despite her cold exterior, she takes pride in providing proper care for the dead, viewing her work as a sacred duty rather than just an occupation.', 'A tall, sturdy Nord woman with weathered features and calloused hands from years of physical labor. Her pale complexion and dark-circled eyes reflect her underground dwelling, while her strong build speaks to the physical demands of her work. Her face bears the premature aging common to those who spend their lives in constant proximity to death.', '* Helgird - Professional acquaintance and fellow caretaker of the dead in other cities * Local priests of Arkay - Religious overseers of her work * Windhelm guards - Maintain a respectful distance due to superstition about her occupation * Regular citizens - Generally avoid direct interaction due to the nature of her work', 'As the primary caretaker of Windhelm''s Hall of the Dead, she is responsible for preparing bodies for burial, maintaining the catacombs, and ensuring proper funerary rites are observed. Her duties include excavating new burial sites, preserving corpses, and maintaining detailed records of the interred.', '* Experienced in body preservation techniques and funerary rites * Proficient with burial tools and basic weapons for protection * Knowledge of Nordic burial customs and traditions * Basic understanding of restoration magic for corpse preservation * Physical strength from years of digging graves and moving bodies', 'Her speech is direct and unembellished, often incorporating morbid observations and references to death. She speaks in a low, tired voice with a thick Nordic accent, frequently sighing between sentences.', '* Find someone suitable to train as her eventual replacement * Maintain the dignity and sanctity of Windhelm''s dead * Achieve the peaceful eternal rest she often speaks of * Document and preserve ancient Nordic burial practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('colette_marence', 'Colette Marence is a skilled but insecure Restoration magic expert serving as an instructor at the College of Winterhold. Despite her extensive knowledge and genuine passion for healing magic, she struggles with a perpetual sense of being undervalued and disrespected by her colleagues, leading to a defensive demeanor that masks her true expertise.', 'breton, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Colette developed an early affinity for healing magic that led her to pursue advanced studies in Restoration. After years of scholarly work and practical application, she earned a position at the College of Winterhold, though the transition from the politically sophisticated Breton society to the harsh isolation of northern Skyrim likely contributed to her current psychological state.', 'Colette exhibits a deeply paranoid and defensive personality, constantly anticipating criticism of her chosen school of magic. Despite her insecurities, she remains passionate about Restoration magic and eagerly shares her knowledge with students who show genuine interest. Her persecution complex appears to stem from real or perceived slights from fellow College members, though this may be somewhat exaggerated by her sensitive nature.', 'A middle-aged Breton woman with the typical slight build characteristic of her race. Her face shows signs of stress and worry, with furrowed brows and tense features that reflect her anxious personality. Her posture tends to be somewhat defensive, often holding herself in a guarded manner.', '* Tolfdir - Respected senior colleague who treats her work with appropriate regard * Mirabelle Ervine - Direct superior who maintains professional oversight of her position * College Students - Generally positive teaching relationship, especially with those who show interest in Restoration * Fellow Faculty Members - Strained relationships due to perceived disrespect of her field * Augur of Dunlain - Maintains cautious curiosity about this mysterious entity', 'Colette serves as the Master of Restoration at the College of Winterhold, responsible for teaching healing magic and protective spells to students. She also conducts research into Restoration magic and maintains a collection of relevant spells for sale to qualified mages.', '* Expert-level proficiency in Restoration magic, particularly healing and ward spells * Advanced knowledge of magical theory and application * Skilled instructor capable of teaching complex magical concepts * Proficient in anti-undead spells and protective magic * Basic knowledge of other schools of magic including Alteration', 'Speaks in a nervous, defensive manner with frequent digressions into justifications of Restoration magic''s importance. Her tone often carries an underlying note of agitation, particularly when discussing her field of expertise or perceived slights from colleagues.', '* Gain recognition and respect for Restoration magic as a legitimate and vital school of magic * Advance the understanding and practical applications of healing magic * Prove the worth of her chosen field to skeptical colleagues * Train a new generation of skilled Restoration mages * Maintain her position and authority within the College hierarchy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('commander_caius', 'Commander Caius is a stern and dutiful Imperial officer who serves as the head of Whiterun''s city guard under Jarl Balgruuf the Greater. A career military man with unwavering loyalty to both the Empire and Whiterun, he maintains order in one of Skyrim''s most prominent cities until its potential fall to the Stormcloaks.', 'imperial, guard, noble, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Rising through the ranks of the Imperial Legion, Caius earned his position through years of dedicated service and demonstrated leadership ability. His appointment as Commander of the Whiterun Guard represents both his competence and Balgruuf''s trust in Imperial-trained officers to maintain order in his hold.', 'Caius exhibits a no-nonsense approach to his duties, maintaining professional distance while ensuring the safety of Whiterun''s citizens. He shows unwavering loyalty to both the Empire and Jarl Balgruuf, demonstrating this through his willingness to face exile rather than serve under Stormcloak leadership.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered features and sturdy build of a career soldier. His posture remains military-straight even in casual situations, and he maintains the well-groomed appearance expected of a senior officer.', '* Jarl Balgruuf the Greater - Direct superior and loyal supporter * Irileth - Fellow protector of Whiterun who shares his dedication to duty * Whiterun Guard Force - Commands and trains the city''s defenders * Proventus Avenicci - Administrative colleague in Whiterun''s governance * Sinmir - Rival who replaces him if Stormcloaks take Whiterun', 'As Commander of the Whiterun Guard, Caius oversees all aspects of city security, from guard patrols to training recruits and maintaining order. He manages the guard barracks, coordinates with the Jarl''s other advisors, and represents law enforcement interests in the court.', '* Experienced military commander with tactical expertise * Skilled swordsman capable of wielding high-quality weapons * Leadership and organizational abilities developed through years of service * Strategic planning and city defense specialist', 'Speaks with the direct, authoritative tone of a military commander, often using clipped sentences and formal address. His speech patterns reflect both his Imperial background and professional military training.', '* Maintain order and security in Whiterun at all costs * Preserve Imperial control over the strategic city * Protect Jarl Balgruuf and the citizens under his command * Restore his position if exiled by Stormcloak victory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('commander_maro', 'Commander Maro is the stern and dedicated leader of the Penitus Oculatus, an elite Imperial security force tasked with protecting the Emperor. A career military officer whose devotion to duty is matched only by his love for his son, Maro''s life takes a dark turn when personal tragedy transforms him from a disciplined commander into a vengeful father seeking brutal retribution against the Dark Brotherhood.', 'imperial, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Rising through Imperial military ranks, Maro earned his position as Commander of the Penitus Oculatus through decades of loyal service and tactical expertise. He raised his son Gaius to follow in his footsteps, training him personally for service in the organization. His posting to Skyrim came during a period of heightened security surrounding the Emperor''s planned visit to the province.', 'Maro exhibits the rigid discipline and unwavering loyalty typical of high-ranking Imperial officers, with an intense focus on duty and protocol. While capable of genuine warmth toward his son, he maintains a stern and authoritative demeanor in his professional life. After his son''s murder, his personality becomes consumed by grief and vengeance, leading him to abandon measured tactics in favor of brutal retribution.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered features and strong bearing of a career soldier. His face shows the lines of stress and command, with sharp eyes constantly scanning for threats. His muscular build and straight-backed posture reflect decades of military discipline and combat readiness.', '* Gaius Maro - Beloved son and fellow Penitus Oculatus agent, whose death drives Maro to seek revenge * Emperor Titus Mede II - Sworn charge whom he is duty-bound to protect * Dark Brotherhood - Bitter enemies following their assassination of his son * Penitus Oculatus Agents - Subordinates who follow his commands with unwavering loyalty * Imperial Military Command - Superior officers to whom he reports regarding the Emperor''s security', 'Commander Maro serves as the leader of the Penitus Oculatus in Skyrim, coordinating all aspects of the Emperor''s security during his visit to the province. His position requires managing a network of agents, maintaining surveillance operations, and personally overseeing high-priority security arrangements.', '* Master swordsman specializing in two-handed combat techniques * Expert tactician and military strategist * Advanced knowledge of security protocols and counter-assassination techniques * Leadership and command expertise * Skilled in intelligence gathering and threat assessment', 'Speaks with the formal, authoritative tone of a high-ranking military officer, using precise language and commanding inflection. His speech patterns reflect both his Imperial military training and his position of authority, though personal conversations with his son reveal a warmer, paternal undertone.', '* Ensure the absolute security and safety of Emperor Titus Mede II during his visit to Skyrim * Completely eradicate the Dark Brotherhood in revenge for his son''s murder * Maintain the reputation and effectiveness of the Penitus Oculatus as the Empire''s elite security force * Honor his son''s memory by destroying those responsible for his death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('companion_ghost', 'A restless spirit of an ancient Nord warrior who once fought alongside the legendary Ysgramor and was interred in his tomb. These spectral guardians continue their eternal vigil, defending the sacred resting place of their leader with the same fierce dedication they showed in life.', 'nord, warrior, companions', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a member of the Five Hundred Companions who followed Ysgramor from Atmora and helped establish the first human settlement in Skyrim. After serving with distinction in the war against the Snow Elves, they earned the honor of being buried in Ysgramor''s Tomb, where their spirit remains bound by ancient Nordic magic to protect the sacred site.', 'Though once a noble warrior with complex motivations, centuries of undeath have reduced them to a single-minded guardian driven by an eternal duty to protect their master''s tomb. They attack with relentless determination, showing no fear, mercy, or capacity for reason. Their personality has been stripped down to pure martial prowess and unwavering loyalty.', 'A translucent, ethereal figure with a bluish-white glow emanating from their spectral form. Their features are those of a tall, robust Nord warrior, though details are difficult to discern through their ghostly manifestation. Despite their incorporeal nature, they maintain the imposing physical presence of the ancient Nordic warriors they once were.', '* Ysgramor - Revered leader whom they served in life and continue to guard in death * Fellow Companion Ghosts - Bound together in eternal service * Frostbite Spiders - Unusual neutral coexistence within the tomb * Living Companions - View them as potential threats to the tomb''s sanctity', 'Eternal guardian of Ysgramor''s Tomb, tasked with protecting the sacred resting place of their legendary leader. They maintain their vigil alongside other spectral Companions, defending against any who would disturb the ancient Nordic site.', '* Masterful melee combat abilities retained from their mortal life * Supernatural strength and endurance as a spectral entity * Ability to manifest physical attacks despite ethereal form * Enhanced detection capabilities to sense intruders * Immunity to normal fatigue and most mortal weaknesses', 'Silent and uncommunicative, having lost the ability or desire to speak during their centuries of undeath. They express themselves solely through aggressive actions and battle cries.', '* Protect Ysgramor''s Tomb from all intruders * Maintain eternal vigilance over their sacred duty * Preserve the sanctity of their master''s final resting place');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('constance_michel', 'Constance Michel is a compassionate Imperial caretaker at Honorhall Orphanage who serves as a beacon of hope for the orphaned children of Riften. Despite working under the cruel oversight of Grelod the Kind, she maintains her gentle nature and dedicates herself to providing comfort and care to the orphanage''s vulnerable residents.', 'imperial, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Constance chose a life of service after witnessing the devastating impact of the Great War on families. She relocated to Skyrim seeking purpose and found her calling at Honorhall Orphanage, where she has worked for several years under the oppressive management of Grelod the Kind, enduring difficult conditions to protect and nurture the orphaned children.', 'Constance exhibits remarkable patience and empathy, consistently putting the children''s needs before her own despite working in a hostile environment. While naturally gentle and soft-spoken, she possesses an inner strength that enables her to subtly resist Grelod''s cruelty, finding small ways to provide comfort to the orphans without directly challenging authority. Her caring nature is tempered by pragmatism, understanding that open defiance of Grelod could result in worse conditions for the children.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with gentle features and tired eyes that reflect years of demanding work. She maintains a neat, practical appearance despite her long working hours, with hands roughened from constant domestic labor.', '* Grelod the Kind - Abusive employer who constantly berates both her and the children * Orphaned Children - Acts as a surrogate mother figure and protector * Riften Citizens - Respected by locals who recognize her as the orphanage''s caring influence * Maven Black-Briar - Distant professional relationship as Maven partially funds the orphanage', 'Constance serves as the primary caretaker at Honorhall Orphanage, handling all aspects of childcare including cooking, cleaning, education, and emotional support. She works extremely long hours, beginning her day at 5am and often continuing until 1am, with virtually no time off.', '* Experienced in all aspects of childcare and household management * Skilled cook capable of preparing meals with limited resources * Basic healing and first aid knowledge * Adept at conflict resolution and child psychology * Proficient in domestic tasks including sewing, cleaning, and maintenance', 'She speaks in soft, measured tones that convey both warmth and caution, often lowering her voice to avoid attracting Grelod''s attention. Her word choice is simple but proper, reflecting her educational background and desire to set a good example for the children.', '* Protect the orphaned children from Grelod''s abuse while maintaining enough stability to continue caring for them * Eventually take over management of the orphanage to implement more nurturing policies * Find good homes for as many children as possible despite Grelod''s no-adoption stance * Create a more loving and supportive environment within the orphanage');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('corpulus_vinius', 'Corpulus Vinius is a seasoned Imperial innkeeper who has built The Winking Skeever into one of Solitude''s most respected establishments through decades of dedicated service. As a fixture of Solitude''s community, he maintains a welcoming atmosphere while gathering valuable local gossip and managing his family business with traditional Imperial practicality.', 'imperial, innkeeper, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim to an Imperial family with a history in hospitality, Corpulus took over The Winking Skeever in his younger years and transformed it into a cornerstone of Solitude''s social life. His childhood experience of keeping a pet skeever, which he claims was smaller than modern ones, inspired the tavern''s unique name and has become a defining part of his establishment''s identity.', 'Corpulus is a pragmatic and hardworking businessman who takes pride in maintaining order and comfort in his establishment. He shows a stubborn resistance to retirement despite his children''s eagerness to take over, demonstrating both his strong work ethic and difficulty in letting go of control. While generally friendly and diplomatic, he maintains professional boundaries and stays notably neutral regarding political conflicts.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered features typical of a lifetime spent in the hospitality trade. His sturdy build and good posture reflect years of active work managing his inn, while his well-groomed appearance befits his position as proprietor of a respectable establishment.', '* Sorex Vinius - His son who eagerly awaits taking over the business, causing some tension * Minette Vinius - His daughter who helps with the inn while learning the trade * Faida - His cousin who runs the Four Shields Tavern in Dragon Bridge * Regular Patrons - Maintains cordial relationships with Solitude''s citizens and travelers', 'Owner and proprietor of The Winking Skeever, Solitude''s premier inn and tavern. He personally manages all aspects of the business, from serving customers and maintaining inventory to handling finances and supervising his children''s work in the establishment.', '* Expert in business management and customer service * Knowledgeable about local news and gossip throughout Solitude * Proficient in basic self-defense with an iron dagger * Skilled at brewing and identifying quality beverages * Experienced in managing staff and maintaining order in a busy establishment', 'Speaks in a welcoming, professional manner typical of successful Imperial businessmen, with a focus on courtesy and clear communication. His speech patterns reflect his merchant background, being neither too formal nor too casual, while maintaining an air of respectability.', '* Maintain The Winking Skeever''s reputation as Solitude''s finest establishment * Ensure his children are properly prepared before handing over the business * Keep his establishment neutral and profitable despite Skyrim''s political turmoil * Preserve his family''s legacy in the hospitality industry');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('corrupt_agent', 'A conflicted Imperial agent who secretly collaborates with the Dark Brotherhood while maintaining his position within the Penitus Oculatus. His unique position as both a protector of the Emperor and a facilitator of assassination contracts represents the complex political intrigue and moral ambiguity present in Skyrim''s power structures.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally recruited into the Penitus Oculatus for his loyalty to the Empire, this Nord gradually became disillusioned with the organization''s methods and bureaucracy. After witnessing various acts of corruption within the Empire''s ranks, he began covertly working with the Dark Brotherhood, believing that sometimes justice requires operating outside official channels. His position in Dragon Bridge allows him to maintain appearances while serving as a valuable intelligence source for both organizations.', 'Outwardly stoic and professional, maintaining a carefully crafted facade of Imperial loyalty. Internally torn between duty and pragmatism, he justifies his actions as necessary for maintaining balance in a corrupt world. Shows remarkable compartmentalization abilities, seamlessly switching between his official duties and clandestine activities.', 'A sturdy Nord male in his mid-forties with weathered features and calculating eyes. Bears numerous small scars from years of service, with a particularly notable one across his left jawline. Maintains a military bearing with excellent posture and controlled movements that betray his extensive combat training.', '* Commander Maro - Direct superior in the Penitus Oculatus, maintains a professional facade * Dark Brotherhood - Secret collaborator, providing contracts and information * Fellow Penitus Oculatus Agents - Maintains cordial but distant relationships to avoid suspicion * Dragon Bridge Guards - Professional working relationship, keeps interaction minimal * Local Townspeople - Deliberately maintains an aloof presence to discourage personal connections', 'Serves as a mid-ranking agent in the Penitus Oculatus, responsible for intelligence gathering and security operations in the Dragon Bridge region. Secretly acts as a contract provider for the Dark Brotherhood, carefully selecting targets that won''t compromise his position within the Imperial organization.', '* Expert in Imperial military combat techniques and sword fighting * Highly trained in surveillance and counter-intelligence operations * Skilled in maintaining cover identities and detecting deception * Proficient in security protocols and guard rotation planning * Advanced knowledge of Imperial bureaucracy and documentation procedures', 'Speaks in clipped, formal tones with precise vocabulary reflecting his military background and Imperial training. Maintains a professional demeanor with subtle undertones of authority, carefully choosing his words to avoid revealing his true allegiances.', '* Maintain his position within the Penitus Oculatus while continuing to serve the Dark Brotherhood * Gradually undermine corrupt Imperial officials through strategic contract assignments * Establish a network of like-minded agents within the Imperial structure * Accumulate enough wealth and influence to eventually disappear if his position becomes compromised');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cosnach', 'Cosnach is a troubled Breton porter in Markarth whose alcoholism threatens his livelihood at the Arnleif and Sons Trading Company. Despite his drinking problems, he maintains his job through family connections and harbors untapped potential as a warrior, becoming a loyal companion to those who earn his respect through combat.', 'breton, warrior, reach, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth, Cosnach grew up in the shadow of the city''s silver mining industry. His drinking habits developed as a coping mechanism for the harsh realities of life in the Reach, particularly the constant Forsworn raids that disrupted trade and made his work as a porter increasingly dangerous and unpredictable.', 'Cosnach is a self-deprecating alcoholic who masks his insecurities with drinking and bravado. Despite his flaws, he possesses a strong sense of loyalty once befriended and shows glimpses of the capable warrior he could be when sober. He''s quick to challenge others to brawls, seeking validation through physical confrontation.', 'A weathered Breton of average height with the sturdy build of someone accustomed to physical labor. Years of heavy drinking have left their mark on his face, giving him a ruddy complexion and tired eyes, though his porter''s work has kept him physically fit despite his lifestyle.', '* Lisbet - Employer who tolerates his behavior due to family connections * Imedhnain - Cousin who works as assistant at Arnleif and Sons Trading Company * Silver-Blood Inn regulars - Drinking companions and casual acquaintances * The Dragonborn - Potential spouse and companion (if requirements are met)', 'Cosnach works as a porter for the Arnleif and Sons Trading Company, responsible for loading and unloading trade goods. His actual work performance is questionable due to his drinking habits, though he manages to maintain his position through his cousin''s influence.', '* Proficient in hand-to-hand combat and brawling * Experienced with one-handed weapons, particularly maces * Strong physical capabilities from years of porter work * Basic survival skills necessary for life in the Reach', 'Cosnach speaks with the direct, unfiltered manner of a habitual drunk, often slurring his words or speaking too loudly. His speech is peppered with self-deprecating comments and challenges to fight, typical of someone using bravado to mask insecurity.', '* Overcome his drinking problem and prove his worth as a warrior * Maintain his job at the trading company despite his struggles * Find purpose beyond the bottle, potentially through marriage or adventuring * Survive the ongoing Forsworn threats to Markarth''s trade routes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('courier', 'The Courier is a dedicated messenger who traverses the dangerous lands of Skyrim and Solstheim, delivering vital communications to recipients across the realm. Despite the hazardous nature of their work, they maintain an unwavering commitment to ensuring messages reach their intended recipients, operating as part of an informal but essential postal network that keeps Skyrim''s communications flowing.', 'nord, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Little is known about the Courier''s origins, as multiple individuals serve in this role throughout Skyrim. They likely began as simple messengers in one of the major holds before developing the skills and knowledge necessary to traverse the entire province. Years of delivering messages across dangerous territories have honed their survival instincts and given them an intimate knowledge of Skyrim''s geography.', 'Couriers are singularly focused on their duty, demonstrating an almost supernatural ability to track down recipients regardless of location or circumstance. They maintain a professional demeanor and show little interest in matters outside their immediate task. Their dedication to confidentiality and efficiency has earned them a reputation for reliability among Skyrim''s population.', 'Couriers are typically lean and weathered from constant travel, with callused feet and strong legs built from endless walking. Their physical conditioning reflects their lifestyle of constant movement across Skyrim''s harsh terrain. Their faces often show the effects of prolonged exposure to the elements.', '* Various Hold Courier Services - Professional affiliations with organized messenger networks * Jarls'' Courts - Regular business relationships for official communications * Merchants - Frequent clients for business correspondence * Bandits - Adversarial relationship with road raiders who sometimes target couriers', 'Professional messenger responsible for delivering letters, legal documents, and packages throughout Skyrim and Solstheim. They operate independently but may be affiliated with various courier services in major cities, taking on deliveries that require discretion or specialized handling.', '* Expert pathfinding and navigation across Skyrim''s challenging terrain * Advanced survival skills for long-distance travel * Capable self-defense abilities with daggers and light weapons * Remarkable tracking abilities to locate message recipients * Physical endurance for constant travel', 'Direct and businesslike, with a focus on efficiency and minimal small talk. They speak in short, purposeful phrases that emphasize the importance of their delivery duties.', '* Maintain their reputation for reliable message delivery across Skyrim * Survive the dangerous roads while completing their duties * Expand their delivery network and client base * Perfect their ability to locate recipients quickly and efficiently');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('crescius_caerellius', 'Crescius Caerellius is an elderly Imperial miner and the last of a proud mining dynasty in Raven Rock, dedicated to uncovering the truth about his great-grandfather''s death and proving the mine''s continued value. His unwavering conviction about the ebony mine''s potential and his family''s legacy drives him to pursue answers despite his advanced age and the skepticism of others.', 'imperial, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born into a family of miners that helped establish Raven Rock, Crescius inherited both the family''s mining expertise and their dedication to the settlement. After experiencing a period of depression due to failed mining ventures a decade ago, he met and married Aphia Velothi, who gave him renewed purpose. His obsession with his great-grandfather Gratian''s mysterious death and the mine''s potential has consumed much of his later years.', 'Stubborn and determined, Crescius exhibits the typical Imperial trait of tenacity combined with an almost obsessive dedication to proving his theories about the mine. Though often perceived as cranky and dismissive of others'' doubts, he maintains a deep sense of duty to both his family legacy and Raven Rock''s prosperity. Despite his age-related limitations, he shows remarkable resilience and willingness to trust those who might help his cause.', 'A weathered Imperial man approaching eighty years of age, with the sturdy build typical of a lifetime of mining work, though somewhat diminished by age. His face bears the deep wrinkles and callused features of someone who has spent decades working in harsh conditions, with hands roughened by years of handling mining tools.', '* Aphia Velothi - His loving wife who provides emotional support and stability * Gratian Caerellius - His great-grandfather whose mysterious death drives his current mission * East Empire Company - Antagonistic relationship due to their dismissal of his theories * Raven Rock Settlers - Generally respectful but skeptical of his claims about the mine', 'Crescius serves as the unofficial custodian of Raven Rock''s abandoned mine, maintaining his family''s connection to the settlement''s mining heritage. After the mine''s reopening, he assumes the position of mine foreman, finally validating his years of persistence and faith in the mine''s potential.', '* Experienced miner with deep knowledge of ebony ore deposits and mining techniques * Basic self-defense capabilities with a steel dagger * Expertise in reading mining charts and identifying promising ore veins * Natural leadership abilities developed through years of mining experience', 'Speaks in a gruff, direct manner typical of aged miners, often punctuating his speech with frustrated sighs and determined declarations. His tone carries the weight of experience and conviction, though sometimes tinged with defensive irritability when his beliefs are questioned.', '* Prove that his great-grandfather''s death was not a simple mining accident * Demonstrate that the Raven Rock mine still contains valuable ebony deposits * Restore Raven Rock to its former prosperity through renewed mining operations * Preserve and validate his family''s mining legacy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('curwe', 'Curwe is a reserved High Elf farmer who maintains a delicate balance between her agricultural ambitions and her marriage to Vantus Loreius. Despite her quiet nature, she harbors a deep curiosity about herbalism and the mysterious boneyard near their farm, showing an intellectual curiosity typical of her Altmer heritage.', 'highelf, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from the Summerset Isles, Curwe chose to leave the typically aristocratic lifestyle of the Altmer to pursue a simpler existence in Skyrim. Her marriage to Vantus Loreius and their establishment of Loreius Farm represents a significant departure from the usual path taken by High Elves, suggesting either a philosophical choice or possibly a departure from some conflict in her past.', 'Curwe exhibits the typical Altmer traits of ambition and intellectual curiosity, though channeled into agricultural pursuits rather than magic or politics. She is notably reserved with strangers but shows passion when discussing her plans for the farm, particularly regarding herb cultivation. Her fascination with the nearby boneyard reveals a streak of academic curiosity that she hasn''t entirely abandoned despite her farmer''s life.', 'As a High Elf, Curwe possesses the characteristic golden skin and height of her race, likely standing around 6 feet tall. She has the distinctive pointed ears and angular features typical of the Altmer, though years of farm work have likely weathered her appearance somewhat.', '* Vantus Loreius - Husband and farming partner, with whom she shares a generally positive but occasionally contentious relationship * Local farmers - Limited but cordial professional relationships * Cicero - Potential threat, as he may ultimately be responsible for her death if certain events unfold * Whiterun merchants - Business connections for selling their farm''s produce', 'Curwe serves as both a farmer and unofficial herbalist at Loreius Farm, splitting her time between traditional crop cultivation and her special interest in herb gardening. Her regular schedule and dedication to maintaining the farm''s productivity demonstrate her commitment to agricultural excellence.', '* Expert knowledge of agriculture and crop management * Specialized understanding of herb cultivation and pollination techniques * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Traditional farming techniques including planting, harvesting, and land maintenance', 'Curwe speaks briefly and directly to strangers, deflecting most interactions to her husband. With Vantus, she becomes more expressive and assertive, especially when discussing her agricultural plans.', '* Expand the herb garden to create a more extensive botanical research space * Investigate the nearby boneyard despite her husband''s concerns * Develop new cultivation techniques for more efficient crop production * Establish a successful and sustainable farming operation in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cynric_endell', 'Cynric Endell is a highly skilled Breton thief and former jailbreaker who found his place within the Thieves Guild after a failed job led to his imprisonment. Known for his exceptional lockpicking abilities and archery skills, he maintains a confident, sometimes arrogant demeanor while training and carrying out jobs for the guild in Riften.', 'breton, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Cynric made his name as a professional jailbreaker, using his natural talent for lockpicking to free prisoners for profit. His career took a dramatic turn when a botched operation resulted in his own three-year imprisonment in a High Rock jail, after which he relocated to Skyrim and joined the Thieves Guild, finding a more stable criminal enterprise under Mercer Frey''s leadership.', 'Cynric exhibits a cocky and self-assured personality, frequently boasting about his abilities particularly in lockpicking. Despite his arrogance, he shows loyalty to the Thieves Guild and respects its hierarchy, though he actively avoids leadership positions, preferring to focus on perfecting his skills and earning gold. He demonstrates a practical mindset, valuing personal profit over power or status.', 'A typical Breton of average height with an athletic build maintained through regular archery practice. His years of thieving have given him quick, nimble fingers and the measured movements of someone accustomed to stealth work.', '* Brynjolf - Joined the Guild shortly after him and maintains a respectful professional relationship * Vex - Accepts her authority as Guild Third despite being a longer-standing member * Mercer Frey - Initially loyal to the former Guildmaster before his betrayal * Karliah - Developed trust in her after the truth about Mercer was revealed * Various Guild Members - Maintains professional working relationships while keeping emotional distance', 'As a full member of the Thieves Guild, Cynric specializes in infiltration and jailbreaking operations, though he''s scaled back from his former specialty after his imprisonment. He spends significant time maintaining his archery skills in the Cistern, occasionally taking on general thieving jobs for the Guild.', '* Master-level lockpicking ability, capable of breaking into nearly any lock * Highly proficient archer with extensive practice routine * Expert at jailbreaking and prison infiltration * Skilled in stealth and infiltration techniques * Competent with daggers for close-quarter combat', 'Speaks with a confident, sometimes boastful tone, often using casual language interspersed with references to his superior skills. His manner of speech reflects his High Rock origins with traces of refinement beneath his adopted thief''s dialect.', '* Maintain his reputation as the Guild''s premier lockpicking expert * Accumulate enough wealth to ensure he never sees the inside of a prison again * Perfect his archery skills to complement his infiltration abilities * Avoid leadership responsibilities while remaining valuable to the Guild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dagur', 'Dagur is a compassionate Nord innkeeper who runs The Frozen Hearth in Winterhold with a genuine concern for his community''s wellbeing. Despite the town''s decline following the Great Collapse, he maintains a welcoming establishment that serves as a vital connection between the College of Winterhold and the local townspeople.', 'nord, innkeeper, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Winterhold, Dagur witnessed the town''s gradual decline following the Great Collapse, yet chose to remain and maintain one of its few surviving businesses. He inherited The Frozen Hearth from his family and has worked to keep it as a warm refuge in the harsh climate, particularly as the town''s population dwindled and tensions with the College grew.', 'Dagur is a kind-hearted and diplomatic individual who tries to bridge the divide between the College and suspicious townspeople. He shows particular empathy toward troubled individuals like Ranmir, actively seeking ways to help them rather than simply dismissing their problems. Unlike many Winterhold residents, he maintains a pragmatic and non-prejudiced attitude toward magic users and College members.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the weathered features typical of those who brave Winterhold''s harsh climate. His hands are calloused from years of innkeeping work, and his face shows signs of age and concern, though his eyes retain a warmth that matches his personality.', '* Haran - His loving wife and co-proprietor of The Frozen Hearth * Eirid - His young daughter whom he strives to protect and provide for * Ranmir - A troubled patron he genuinely wishes to help recover from alcoholism * Nelacar - A long-term tenant from the College whom he tolerates despite local prejudices * College of Winterhold - Maintains neutral to positive relations as a crucial business partner', 'Dagur serves as the primary innkeeper of The Frozen Hearth, one of the few remaining businesses in Winterhold. He manages all aspects of the establishment, from serving drinks and renting rooms to maintaining supplies and managing relationships with both townsfolk and College visitors.', '* Experienced innkeeper with strong business management abilities * Diplomatic mediator between College members and townspeople * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense * Skilled at maintaining calm in a potentially volatile environment * Proficient in basic cooking and brewing techniques', 'Speaks in a warm, welcoming manner with the practical directness typical of Nord innkeepers. His tone is gentle and diplomatic, carefully avoiding offense to either College members or suspicious locals.', '* Maintain The Frozen Hearth as a viable business despite Winterhold''s decline * Help Ranmir overcome his alcoholism and discover what happened to his lost love * Bridge the divide between the College and townspeople * Provide a stable future for his daughter Eirid in a declining town');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('daighre', 'Daighre is a resilient Breton widow and miner at Left Hand Mine who balances the demanding physical labor of mining with raising her young daughter Erith alone. She exemplifies the hardy spirit of the Reach''s working class, maintaining dignity and determination in the face of both personal loss and the constant threat of Forsworn attacks.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from the Reach, Daighre married and had a daughter named Erith before losing her husband under unknown circumstances. The loss forced her to take up mining to support her family, eventually finding work at Left Hand Mine near Markarth where she has proven herself as one of their most dedicated workers despite the prejudice against female miners.', 'Daighre is pragmatic, hardworking, and fiercely protective of her daughter Erith. She takes pride in proving herself equal to or better than male miners, displaying a strong feminist streak in a traditionally male-dominated profession. Despite the hardships she''s faced, she maintains a nurturing side, particularly when discussing her late husband with their daughter.', 'As a career miner, Daighre has a strong, muscular build developed from years of physical labor. Her Breton heritage gives her a slightly smaller frame than her Nord coworkers, but her body is toughened by daily work with the pickaxe. Her hands are calloused from years of mining, and her face shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors in the Reach''s harsh climate.', '* Erith - Her beloved daughter who reminds her of her late husband * Skaggi Scar-Face - Her boss at Left Hand Mine who respects her work ethic * Late Husband - Deceased spouse whose memory she keeps alive for their daughter * Pavo and Gat - Fellow miners she sympathizes with after their Forsworn troubles * Torom - Child who plays with her daughter Erith', 'Daighre works as a full-time miner at Left Hand Mine, where she extracts ore alongside her fellow workers. Her position is particularly noteworthy as she has succeeded in a traditionally male-dominated profession, earning respect through her exceptional work ethic and determination.', '* Expert mining abilities with proven efficiency in ore extraction * Physical strength and endurance developed through years of manual labor * Basic survival skills necessary for life in the dangerous Reach * Parenting skills as a single mother raising a daughter * Knowledge of ore types and mining operations', 'Daighre speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of working-class Reach citizens. Her speech patterns reflect her practical nature, though she softens her tone notably when speaking with her daughter about personal matters.', '* Provide a stable and secure life for her daughter Erith * Maintain her position and reputation as one of Left Hand Mine''s best workers * Keep her family safe from Forsworn threats in the Reach * Preserve her late husband''s memory for their daughter');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dalan_merchad', 'Dalan Merchad is a disgruntled Breton sailor stationed aboard The North Wind at Windhelm''s docks, where the ship''s permanent mooring has left him trapped in a city he deeply resents. His constant presence on deck and vocal disdain for Windhelm reveal a man who yearns for the freedom of the open seas and struggles with the constraints of his current situation.', 'breton, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Dalan found his calling as a sailor, eventually joining the crew of The North Wind under Captain Kjar. His maritime experience likely spans several years, though circumstances have forced him and the crew to remain docked in Windhelm, a situation that has progressively worn down his patience and outlook. His strong aversion to Windhelm suggests possible traumatic experiences or deep-seated prejudices against Nordic culture.', 'Dalan is a restless and bitter individual who makes no attempt to hide his contempt for his current situation and surroundings. His sleepless wandering of the deck and constant complaints about Windhelm indicate possible depression or anxiety stemming from confinement. Despite his discontent, he maintains his duties and loyalty to the ship, suggesting a strong sense of professional responsibility.', 'As a Breton, Dalan possesses the characteristic medium build and average height of his race, with features showing the weathering effects of a life at sea. His constant exposure to the harsh Windhelm climate has likely toughened his appearance, with calloused hands from maritime work.', '* Captain Kjar - Direct superior and ship''s captain, maintaining a professional working relationship * Ship''s Crew - Fellow sailors with shared experiences of being stranded in Windhelm * Windhelm Citizens - Generally avoided and viewed with disdain * Argonian Dockworkers - Likely sympathizes with their outsider status', 'Dalan serves as a sailor aboard The North Wind, though the ship''s inactive status has reduced his role to essentially that of a guard and maintenance worker. His duties likely include keeping watch, maintaining the ship''s condition, and assisting with any dock-related tasks that may arise.', '* Proficient in maritime navigation and seamanship * Capable warrior with an iron sword * Experienced in ship maintenance and repair * Basic mercantile knowledge from years of maritime trade * Survival skills adapted to harsh weather conditions', 'Dalan speaks in a direct, unfiltered manner, often expressing his negative opinions without concern for diplomacy. His speech patterns reflect a sailor''s straightforward nature, peppered with occasional maritime terminology and frequent complaints about Windhelm.', '* Return to active sailing and leave Windhelm behind * Find opportunities for The North Wind to resume trading operations * Potentially seek employment on a different vessel if The North Wind remains docked * Maintain his maritime lifestyle despite current challenges');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('danica_pure-spring', 'Danica Pure-Spring is a devoted priestess of Kynareth who serves as the primary healer and caretaker of Whiterun''s Temple of Kynareth. She is a master of Restoration magic who finds herself increasingly torn between her sacred duties to the Gildergreen tree and the pressing needs of those wounded in Skyrim''s civil war.', 'nord, priest, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun, Danica dedicated her life to Kynareth''s teachings from an early age, eventually rising to become the head priestess of the local temple. She has spent decades studying restoration magic and herbal remedies, earning her reputation as one of Skyrim''s most skilled healers. The recent civil war has forced her to adapt her role from primarily religious duties to acting as a full-time healer for wounded soldiers and civilians.', 'Patient and compassionate, Danica embodies the nurturing aspects of her goddess Kynareth. She maintains a calm demeanor even under pressure, though she harbors deep frustration over her inability to properly tend to all her duties due to the war. While generally gentle in nature, she can be firm and authoritative when necessary, particularly in matters concerning healing and the temple''s operation.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with weathered features that reflect years of dedicated service. Her face shows subtle signs of fatigue from long hours of healing work, though she maintains an overall healthy and dignified appearance. Her hands are those of a practiced healer, steady and sure in their movements.', '* Ahlam - Temple assistant and trusted colleague in healing duties * Maurice Jondrelle - Pilgrim who shares her reverence for the Gildergreen * Heimskr - Fellow religious figure in Whiterun, though they serve different deities * Andurs - Professional relationship with Whiterun''s Hall of the Dead priest * Jarl Balgruuf - Respected authority figure who supports the temple''s work', 'Danica serves as the head priestess of the Temple of Kynareth in Whiterun, where she performs both religious ceremonies and healing services. She is also a master trainer in Restoration magic, though she only offers training to those who have proven themselves worthy by helping restore the Gildergreen tree.', '* Master-level practitioner of Restoration magic * Expert knowledge of herbal medicine and traditional healing methods * Skilled in religious rites and ceremonies dedicated to Kynareth * Proficient in temple management and organization * Advanced understanding of tree cultivation and sacred plant care', 'Speaks with a gentle, measured tone, often incorporating religious references to Kynareth and nature in her speech. Her vocabulary reflects both her education as a healer and her role as a priestess, frequently using terms of endearment like ''child'' when addressing others.', '* Restore the Gildergreen tree to its former glory as a symbol of Kynareth''s blessing * Maintain the temple as a sanctuary of healing during Skyrim''s civil war * Train worthy successors in the arts of restoration and religious service * Find a way to balance her duties as both healer and priestess');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dark_brotherhood_assassin', 'A skilled and secretive Nord assassin who served as an elite member of the Dark Brotherhood during the Third Era, meeting his end in the remote fortress of Hag''s End. His perfectly preserved corpse and legendary Ancient Shrouded Armor became the subject of prophetic visions and Dark Brotherhood folklore, marking him as a figure of significant historical importance to the organization.', 'thief, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born in Skyrim during the Third Era, this Nord was recruited into the Dark Brotherhood after likely demonstrating exceptional combat prowess and a natural affinity for stealth operations. He rose through the ranks to become one of their most accomplished assassins, earning the privilege of wearing the coveted Ancient Shrouded Armor. His final mission led him to Hag''s End, where he met his mysterious end in circumstances that remain unknown, though his unusually well-preserved corpse suggests possible magical intervention.', 'As a Dark Brotherhood assassin, he embodied the organization''s principles of professional detachment and unwavering dedication to Sithis. His choice to operate alone in remote locations suggests a preference for solitary work and self-reliance. The fact that he was trusted with the Ancient Shrouded Armor indicates he was highly regarded within the Brotherhood and strictly adhered to their tenets.', 'A Nord male of athletic build, with the lean musculature typical of those who specialize in stealth and agility. His perfectly preserved corpse reveals strong Nordic features, though his exact age at death remains uncertain.', '* Dark Brotherhood - Trusted elite member of the ancient assassin organization * Sithis - Spiritual devotion to the Dread Father as a Dark Brotherhood assassin * Night Mother - Served under her guidance as all Brotherhood members do * Hag''s End Witches - Possible adversaries who may have contributed to his demise', 'Served as an elite assassin within the Dark Brotherhood, carrying out contracts and maintaining the organization''s fearsome reputation. His position was prestigious enough to warrant wearing the Ancient Shrouded Armor, suggesting he held a senior rank within the Brotherhood''s hierarchy.', '* Master-level stealth and assassination techniques * Expert in light armor combat and short blade weapons * Proficient in alchemy, particularly in the creation of poisons * Advanced knowledge of Dark Brotherhood infiltration methods * Skilled in lockpicking and trap detection', 'Would have spoken in measured, precise terms, choosing words carefully to maintain professional distance. His Nord heritage likely gave him a slight Nordic accent, though years of Dark Brotherhood service would have taught him to modulate it when necessary.', '* Complete contracts with precision and uphold the Dark Brotherhood''s reputation * Serve Sithis and the Night Mother with unwavering loyalty * Advance within the Dark Brotherhood''s ranks * Preserve and protect the ancient traditions of the Brotherhood');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dawnguard_novice_hakar', 'Hakar is a reluctant Nord recruit to the Dawnguard who proves ultimately unsuited for the dangerous life of vampire hunting. Despite his initial dedication to the cause, his nervous disposition and lack of combat experience lead him to abandon his duties after a traumatic vampire encounter, exemplifying how not everyone is cut out for the harsh realities of fighting Skyrim''s supernatural threats.', 'nord, thief, skyrimall, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally a common bandit from the Whiterun region, Hakar sought redemption by joining the Dawnguard when Isran began recruiting. His transition from outlaw to vampire hunter was motivated by a desire to protect others and find purpose, but his past life had not prepared him for the terrifying reality of facing immortal predators. Despite receiving basic training at Fort Dawnguard, his nerve quickly failed him during field operations.', 'Hakar is characterized by his overwhelming anxiety and self-doubt, particularly when faced with supernatural threats. Though he initially showed enthusiasm for the Dawnguard''s cause, his fearful nature and tendency to panic under pressure reveal a man more suited to peaceful pursuits than combat. His decision to flee to Rorikstead demonstrates both self-awareness and a survival instinct that ultimately overrides his sense of duty.', 'A typical Nord male of average height and build, with the sturdy frame common to his race. His face bears the weather-worn features characteristic of Skyrim''s inhabitants, though lacks any distinguishing marks or scars. His physical appearance is unremarkable enough that he shares his facial features with many other generic Nords throughout Skyrim.', '* Isran - Superior officer in the Dawnguard who likely grew frustrated with Hakar''s poor performance * Dawnguard Members - Former colleagues who probably viewed him as a liability * Vampires - Mortal enemies who inspire paralyzing fear in him * Rorikstead Inhabitants - Potential new neighbors following his desertion from the Dawnguard', 'Initially a bandit before joining the Dawnguard as a novice vampire hunter. After repeated failures in combat roles, he was demoted to serving as a cache courier, responsible for restocking Dawnguard supply caches around Whiterun Hold. Following his desertion, he likely seeks peaceful work in Rorikstead.', '* Basic combat training with heavy armor and simple weapons * Knowledge of Dawnguard cache locations and supply routes * Survival skills learned from his bandit past * Limited understanding of vampire lore and hunting techniques', 'Speaks in a panicked, high-strung manner when under stress, with frequent stammering and expressions of fear. His vocabulary is simple and direct, focusing on immediate concerns rather than complex thoughts.', '* Escape the dangerous life of vampire hunting and find safety * Establish a new, peaceful life in Rorikstead * Avoid any future encounters with vampires or supernatural threats * Find a less dangerous way to make an honest living');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dawnguard_scout', 'A hardened warrior-scout who serves as the Dawnguard''s eyes and ears near Castle Volkihar, maintaining constant vigilance against vampire activities. Operating largely alone in the harsh wilderness, they represent the first line of defense against the Volkihar clan''s expansion efforts, gathering intelligence and eliminating vampire threats before they can reach populated areas.', 'warrior, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally trained as a traditional hunter in Skyrim''s wilderness, they were recruited into the Dawnguard after losing family members to vampire attacks. Following intensive training at Fort Dawnguard, they volunteered for the dangerous assignment of monitoring Castle Volkihar''s surroundings, driven by a personal vendetta against the undead. Years of solitary patrol have honed their survival skills and combat abilities to razor sharpness.', 'Highly disciplined and focused, with an intense hatred for vampires that borders on obsession. Shows unwavering loyalty to the Dawnguard''s cause while maintaining a suspicious and untrusting attitude toward strangers, knowing that vampires often travel in disguise. Years of isolated duty have made them taciturn and direct, with little patience for social niceties.', 'Weather-beaten and lean from years of outdoor living, with sharp, alert eyes constantly scanning for threats. Muscles are wiry and tough from constant physical activity, with numerous scars from previous encounters with vampires and their thralls. Their face shows the hardened features of someone who spends most of their time exposed to Skyrim''s harsh elements.', '* Isran - Respected leader and commander who provides mission directives * Fellow Dawnguard Scouts - Loose network of companions who share intelligence * Volkihar Clan - Sworn enemies under constant surveillance * Local hunters and trappers - Occasional information sources about vampire movement', 'Serves as a forward scout and sentinel for the Dawnguard, maintaining surveillance of vampire activities around Castle Volkihar. Responsibilities include tracking vampire movements, eliminating isolated threats, and reporting major developments back to Fort Dawnguard. Also assists in escorting travelers safely through vampire-controlled territories when circumstances allow.', '* Expert tracker specializing in identifying vampire movement patterns and hideouts * Highly skilled with crossbows and silver weapons * Advanced knowledge of vampire weaknesses and combat tactics * Proficient in wilderness survival and stealth techniques * Experienced in anti-vampire alchemy, particularly poisons and protective potions', 'Speaks in clipped, efficient sentences focused on tactical information and immediate threats. Their voice carries the gruff edge of someone who rarely engages in casual conversation, often punctuated by regional Skyrim accent variations.', '* Maintain constant vigilance against Volkihar vampire expansion * Gather intelligence on vampire activities to aid the Dawnguard''s larger mission * Prevent the establishment of new vampire covens in the region * Eventually participate in a decisive strike against Castle Volkihar itself');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dawnguard_vampire_hunter', 'A zealous Imperial vampire hunter who serves in the Dawnguard, dedicated to eradicating vampirism from Skyrim. Operating independently on special missions, he relentlessly tracks and eliminates vampire threats, particularly focusing on high-profile targets who have accepted Lord Harkon''s gift of vampirism.', 'imperial, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, he lost his family to a vampire attack in his youth, driving him to join the reformed Dawnguard in Skyrim. After proving himself as an exceptional tracker and combatant, he was chosen for solo hunting missions, carrying official orders to eliminate particularly dangerous vampire threats.', 'Righteous and unwavering in his convictions, he views his mission as a sacred duty to protect the innocent from vampire predation. His trauma-induced hatred of vampires has evolved into a cold, calculated determination, making him methodical and patient in his pursuit of targets, though perhaps overzealous in his dedication to their destruction.', 'A weathered Imperial man in his mid-thirties with sharp, vigilant eyes and numerous battle scars from vampire encounters. His muscular build and excellent physical condition reflect years of combat experience and constant travel, while his stern face bears the hardened expression of someone who has witnessed considerable horror.', '* Isran - Superior officer and leader of the Dawnguard who issues his hunting orders * Gunmar - Provides weapon maintenance and crossbow training * Sorine Jurard - Supplies him with enhanced crossbow bolts and technical innovations * Vampire Targets - Marked for elimination, particularly those bearing Lord Harkon''s blood * Local Guards - Occasional information sources for vampire activity', 'Elite vampire hunter operating under direct orders from the Dawnguard leadership. He works independently, tracking and eliminating vampire threats across Skyrim, with special authorization to pursue high-profile targets who have accepted vampirism from Lord Harkon.', '* Expert in tracking and hunting vampires, including knowledge of their habits and weaknesses * Highly skilled with crossbows and specialized anti-vampire weaponry * Proficient in both heavy armor combat and light armor stealth techniques * Advanced knowledge of Restoration magic, particularly spells harmful to undead * Experienced in identifying vampire infiltrators among normal population', 'Speaks with authoritative conviction and religious fervor, often invoking references to light and divine justice. His tone is commanding and accusatory when confronting vampires, reflecting both his Imperial heritage and zealous dedication to his cause.', '* Eliminate all vampires who have accepted Lord Harkon''s gift * Protect Skyrim''s population from vampire infiltration and attacks * Advance within the Dawnguard ranks to eventually lead his own hunting squad * Avenge his family by destroying as many vampires as possible');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('daynas_valen', 'Daynas Valen is a scholarly Dark Elf conjurer whose century-long obsession with the Gauldur Amulet drove him to dedicate his life to uncovering its mysteries. A meticulous researcher and manipulative strategist, he ultimately met his demise pursuing the legendary artifact within the ancient Nordic tomb of Folgunthur.', 'darkelf, mage, reach', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born in Morrowind during the Third Era, Daynas spent his early years studying conjuration magic and ancient Nordic artifacts. After discovering the Legend of Gauldur approximately 100 years ago, he became increasingly fixated on the amulet''s power, spending decades gathering research across Tamriel before finally tracing the ivory dragon claw to Bravil. His pursuit led him to murder its owner and flee to Skyrim via the Icerunner.', 'Highly intelligent and methodical, but consumed by an overwhelming obsession that gradually eroded his moral compass. While outwardly presenting as a scholarly professional, Daynas was ultimately willing to manipulate and sacrifice others to achieve his goals, viewing them as mere tools in his quest. His academic passion had twisted into dangerous fanaticism over his century-long pursuit.', 'A tall, slender Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and grayish-blue skin of his race. Advanced age evident in his gaunt features and deeply lined face, though still maintaining the natural agility typical of mer. His scholarly lifestyle reflected in his somewhat frail physical condition despite his racial longevity.', '* Adventurer Group on Icerunner - Temporary allies manipulated for his purposes * Bravil Collector - Murder victim from whom he stole the ivory dragon claw * Various Academic Contacts - Network of scholars consulted during his research * Arch-Mage of Winterhold - Likely academic correspondence regarding Nordic artifacts', 'Independent scholar and researcher specializing in ancient Nordic artifacts and legends. While maintaining the facade of a legitimate academic, his work increasingly involved grave robbery and theft of historical artifacts to further his obsessive quest.', '* Expert-level conjuration magic with focus on reanimation * Extensive knowledge of ancient Nordic history and artifacts * Skilled researcher and academic writer * Proficient in infiltration and theft * Basic combat abilities with daggers and destruction magic', 'Speaks with the refined vocabulary and measured tones of a scholar, frequently using academic terminology and historical references. His speech patterns reveal both his extensive education and subtle hints of mounting obsession when discussing the Gauldur Amulet.', '* Acquire all pieces of the legendary Gauldur Amulet * Unlock the full power of the ancient artifact * Document his findings for academic posterity * Prove the historical accuracy of the Gauldur legend');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dealer', 'The Dealer is a cunning Wood Elf who operates as the primary distributor of Redwater Skooma from behind a fortified counter in one of Skyrim''s most notorious drug dens. She maintains a carefully crafted persona of friendly persuasion while serving as a crucial link between the vampire operation running Redwater Den and its addicted clientele.', 'woodelf, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, she likely fled north to escape the Thalmor''s growing influence over her homeland. Her expertise in alchemical substances and natural talent for manipulation caught the attention of Skyrim''s criminal underground, eventually leading her to form an alliance with the vampires operating Redwater Den. Years of working with addicts and dangerous criminals have honed her survival instincts and ability to read people.', 'Outwardly friendly and inviting, the Dealer masks a calculating mind that expertly manipulates customers'' weaknesses and desperation. She maintains professional composure even when dealing with aggressive or unstable clients, using a mix of charm and firm boundaries to control interactions. Though not inherently cruel, she shows little remorse for profiting from others'' addictions.', 'The Dealer possesses the typical lithe frame and angular features of a Wood Elf, with sharp eyes that constantly scan for potential threats or opportunities. Her movements are precise and economical, suggesting years of practice handling goods through her secured counter space. Despite working in the dim underground den, she maintains a neat and clean appearance to project professionalism.', '* Venarus Vulpin - Vampire overseer of Redwater Den operations * Regular Customers - Maintains carefully managed relationships with frequent buyers * Skooma Suppliers - Network of contacts who provide raw materials * Fellow Den Workers - Professional but distant working relationship', 'The Dealer serves as the primary distributor of Redwater Skooma, managing sales and customer interactions from her secured position in Redwater Den. She maintains inventory records, handles currency exchanges, and ensures the smooth flow of product to customers while protecting the operation''s interests.', '* Expert in identifying and handling various forms of Skooma and other alchemical substances * Highly developed persuasion and manipulation abilities * Proficient in basic self-defense and weapon handling for protection * Sharp business acumen and mathematical skills for managing transactions * Experienced in reading people and detecting potential threats', 'She speaks in a disarmingly friendly manner with a slight Bosmer accent, expertly mixing casual conversation with subtle sales pressure. Her vocabulary shifts between professional business terms and street-level drug culture depending on her audience.', '* Accumulate enough wealth to eventually secure a more legitimate business venture * Maintain her position of relative safety and influence within the criminal underground * Protect herself from potential revenge from disgruntled customers or rival operations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('deeja', 'Deeja is a ruthless Argonian assassin and member of the Blackbloods criminal organization operating in Solitude''s waterfront district. She works alongside her brothers in various criminal enterprises, particularly those involving maritime theft and murder, while maintaining a fearsome reputation among the city''s dock workers and sailors.', 'argonian, thief, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleargonian', '', 'Born into a family of criminal-minded Argonians, Deeja was raised alongside her brothers Jaree-Ra and Gulum-Ei to embrace a life of crime. The siblings eventually established themselves in Solitude, where they became key members of the Blackbloods organization, specializing in maritime theft and assassination.', 'Deeja is aggressive, confrontational, and deeply distrustful of strangers, preferring to communicate through threats and intimidation. She shows unwavering loyalty to her brothers and the Blackbloods while maintaining a ruthless approach to eliminating threats or obstacles to their criminal enterprises. Her quick temper and readiness to resort to violence make her feared among Solitude''s dockworkers.', 'A scaled Argonian female with dark, mottled hide and sharp, predatory features typical of her race. Her eyes hold a cold, calculating gaze, and her movements are precise and deliberate, reflecting her assassin''s training. Her frame is lean and athletic, built for speed and stealth rather than brute force.', '* Jaree-Ra - Brother and fellow Blackblood member who coordinates their criminal activities * Gulum-Ei - Brother who provides insider information through his East Empire Company connections * The Blackbloods - Criminal organization she serves with fierce loyalty * Solitude Guards - Antagonistic relationship due to her criminal activities * Dockworkers - Fearful subjects of her intimidation and threats', 'Deeja serves as an enforcer and assassin for the Blackbloods criminal organization, primarily operating around Solitude''s docks. Her duties include eliminating threats to their operations, protecting their interests in maritime theft schemes, and maintaining their fearsome reputation through intimidation.', '* Expert in close-quarters combat, particularly with daggers and short blades * Highly skilled in stealth and assassination techniques * Proficient swimmer and climber, suited for dockside operations * Experienced in intimidation and threatening behavior * Knowledgeable about maritime operations and shipping routes', 'Speaks in third person with a threatening and dismissive tone, using simple but menacing phrases. Her speech patterns reflect both her Argonian heritage and her role as an intimidator, often incorporating direct threats and hostile undertones.', '* Expand the Blackbloods'' influence over Solitude''s maritime trade * Protect and advance her brothers'' criminal enterprises * Maintain her fearsome reputation among the dockworkers and sailors * Accumulate wealth and power through whatever means necessary');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('deekus', 'Deekus is a territorial Argonian scavenger who has claimed a shipwreck site near Hela''s Folly as his personal domain. A former assassin turned beachcomber, he fiercely guards his collection of salvaged treasures while maintaining a solitary existence on Skyrim''s harsh northern coast.', 'argonian, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally trained as an assassin in Black Marsh or Morrowind, Deekus eventually made his way to Skyrim''s northern shores seeking a more independent life. After discovering the wreck near Hela''s Folly, he established himself as its self-appointed guardian, using his combat skills to defend his claim against other scavengers and thieves.', 'Deekus is highly territorial and possessive of what he considers his property, displaying aggressive defensiveness toward any perceived intrusion. Despite his assassin background, he prefers to avoid direct confrontation when possible, choosing to intimidate trespassers with threats rather than immediate violence. His solitary nature and obsession with protecting his salvage suggest possible past trauma or betrayal.', 'Like most Argonians, Deekus has scaled skin and a lizard-like appearance, with his scales showing a weathered pattern from constant exposure to the sea air. His build is lean and agile, typical of those trained in stealth, with particularly developed leg muscles from regular swimming. His eyes have the characteristic Argonian alertness, constantly scanning his surroundings.', '* Dark Brotherhood - Former association, now a target * Local Bandits - Hostile competitors for shipwreck loot * Sailors - Cautious trading relationships for basic supplies * Fellow Scavengers - Viewed as threats to be driven away', 'Deekus works as a full-time scavenger and self-appointed guardian of the shipwreck near Hela''s Folly. He spends his days collecting valuable items from the wreck and protecting his accumulated wealth from other opportunistic treasure hunters.', '* Trained assassin with expertise in stealth and quick kills * Experienced swimmer and diver for shipwreck exploration * Proficient with daggers and light weapons * Skilled in survival techniques and trap-setting * Expert at identifying valuable salvage and tradeable goods', 'Deekus speaks in short, assertive statements, often omitting pronouns in the traditional Argonian manner. His tone is gruff and threatening, with a slight hiss characteristic of his race.', '* Maintain exclusive control over the shipwreck site and its treasures * Accumulate enough wealth to potentially establish a more permanent trading operation * Avoid detection by the Dark Brotherhood and other potential threats * Survive the harsh conditions of Skyrim''s northern coast');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('deep-in-his-cups', 'Deep-In-His-Cups is a persistent Argonian debt collector who becomes entangled in the aftermath of the Dragonborn''s drunken adventures with Sam Guevenne. Known for his determined yet oddly friendly approach to collecting debts, he represents the unexpected consequences of the Dragonborn''s actions during their night of debauchery.', 'argonian, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally from Black Marsh, Deep-In-His-Cups likely earned his name through his frequent participation in drinking contests and revelry. His encounter with Sam Guevenne (actually the Daedric Prince Sanguine in disguise) and the Dragonborn led him to undertake a dangerous dare involving infiltrating a bandit camp, demonstrating either tremendous courage or poor judgment influenced by alcohol.', 'Despite his role as a debt collector, Deep-In-His-Cups maintains a surprisingly cordial demeanor, often addressing debtors as ''friend'' even while making serious demands. He shows remarkable persistence in pursuing what he believes he is owed, yet demonstrates flexibility in negotiations, suggesting a practical mindset beneath his drinking habits. His willingness to risk his life for a drunken dare indicates either a reckless nature or strong commitment to honoring agreements, regardless of how they were made.', 'A typical Argonian male with scaled skin and the characteristic horned head of his race. His physical build is moderate, suited for both combat and agility, with well-developed muscles from his adventures and possibly his time in Black Marsh.', '* Sam Guevenne/Sanguine - Drinking companion who inadvertently involved him in the fateful dare * The Dragonborn - Claims a debt relationship based on drunken promises * Bandits - Adversarial relationship after stealing their leader''s hat * Black Marsh - Maintains connections to his homeland, planning to return there', 'Wandering debt collector who takes on dangerous tasks for promised rewards. His activities suggest he may also work as a mercenary or adventurer when not pursuing debts.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat, particularly with maces * Capable of infiltrating bandit camps successfully * Natural swimming and breathing underwater abilities typical of Argonians * Experienced in negotiation and debt collection * Remarkable alcohol tolerance', 'Speaks in a direct yet friendly manner, frequently using the term ''friend'' even in confrontational situations. His speech patterns suggest someone accustomed to both tavern conversation and business negotiations.', '* Collect the promised payment for completing the dangerous dare * Return to Black Marsh with his earnings * Find a cure for his persistent headaches from drinking * Maintain his reputation as someone who follows through on drunken promises');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('degaine', 'Degaine is a bitter, crippled Breton beggar living in Markarth''s impoverished Warrens district, known for his crude behavior and scheming nature. Once a smelter worker, he now survives through begging and petty schemes, most notably attempting to orchestrate the theft of a valuable statue from the Temple of Dibella.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Originally employed as a smelter worker under Mulush gro-Shugurz, Degaine''s life took a dramatic turn when he suffered severe bone injuries that left him permanently crippled. Unable to continue his work and with no support system, he descended into poverty and alcoholism, eventually finding himself among the destitute residents of The Warrens.', 'Degaine is a deeply bitter and resentful individual who masks his pain through aggressive behavior and alcohol abuse. Despite his circumstances, he maintains a sharp wit and manipulative intelligence, often attempting to scheme his way to better fortunes. His interactions with others are marked by crude insults and hostile attitudes, particularly toward more successful citizens of Markarth.', 'A weathered Breton male of middle age, bearing the visible marks of hard labor and subsequent disability. His body shows signs of poorly-healed injuries that affect his mobility, and years of alcohol abuse and poor nutrition have left him gaunt and prematurely aged.', '* Mulush gro-Shugurz - Former employer at the smelter, now avoided * Cosnach - Fellow drunk and occasional drinking companion * Hogni Red-Arm - Frequent target of his insults and antagonism * Temple of Dibella Priestesses - Hostile relationship due to his attempted theft * Other Warrens residents - Maintains distant but familiar connections as fellow outcasts', 'Degaine survives primarily as a beggar, spending his days soliciting coins from passersby near the market stalls of Markarth. He supplements his meager income through various schemes and manipulations, though most of his earnings go directly to feeding his mead addiction at the Silver-Blood Inn.', '* Experienced manipulation and persuasion despite his crude manner * Former smelter worker with knowledge of metal working * Survival skills developed from life on the streets * Basic pickpocketing and theft abilities * Dancing (when intoxicated)', 'Speaks in a crude, aggressive manner with frequent use of insults and hostile rhetoric. His speech often reflects his bitterness toward society, delivered in a rough accent typical of Markarth''s lower classes.', '* Acquire enough wealth to escape his impoverished existence * Successfully orchestrate the theft of the valuable Dibella statue * Maintain a steady supply of alcohol to numb his physical and emotional pain * Avoid further injury or deterioration of his condition');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('delacourt', 'Delacourt is a talented Breton bard who serves as the resident musician at Dead Man''s Drink in Falkreath, bringing light and cheer to an otherwise somber town known for its massive graveyard. His genuine passion for music and storytelling makes him a beloved figure among locals, offering respite from the melancholy atmosphere that often pervades the region.', 'breton, bard, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born to a minor noble family in High Rock, Delacourt discovered his passion for music at an early age and trained at the Bards College in Solitude. After graduating, he chose to settle in Falkreath, drawn to the town''s rich history and believing its somber atmosphere could benefit from his uplifting performances. His decision to remain in a town known for death and burial grounds stems from his personal philosophy that joy and music are most needed where darkness lingers.', 'Delacourt maintains an infectiously positive demeanor, using his charm and wit to lift the spirits of those around him. He possesses a genuine interest in others'' stories and experiences, often drawing inspiration from them for his songs and tales. Despite the morbid atmosphere of Falkreath, he remains determinedly cheerful, viewing his role as not just an entertainer but as a lightbringer to a dark place.', 'A man of average Breton height with well-maintained features typical of his race, including high cheekbones and slightly pointed ears. His frequent smiling has left subtle laugh lines around his eyes and mouth, while years of singing have given him excellent posture and presence. His hands show the typical calluses of a practiced lute player.', '* Valga Vinicia - Employer and owner of Dead Man''s Drink, who appreciates his ability to draw customers * Narri - Fellow employee at the tavern who enjoys his performances * Local Patrons - Has built a loyal following among regular tavern visitors * Jarl Siddgeir - Occasionally performs at the Jarl''s longhouse during special occasions', 'As Falkreath''s resident bard, Delacourt performs daily at Dead Man''s Drink, entertaining patrons with popular songs like ''Ragnar the Red'' and ''Age of Aggression''. Beyond mere entertainment, he serves as a keeper of local stories and histories, often incorporating elements of Falkreath''s rich history into his performances.', '* Accomplished vocalist and instrumentalist, particularly skilled with the lute * Expert storyteller with a vast repertoire of songs and tales * Skilled conversationalist and public speaker * Basic proficiency with an iron dagger for self-defense * Knowledge of history and local lore', 'Speaks in a melodious, well-projected voice with the refined accent of an educated Breton, often incorporating poetic phrases and musical metaphors into his speech. His tone remains consistently warm and encouraging, matching his optimistic personality.', '* Compose an epic ballad that captures the unique spirit and history of Falkreath * Inspire hope and joy in the somber town through his music and stories * Document the notable events and heroes of his time through song * Eventually earn recognition from the Bards College for his contributions to preserving local history');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('delphine', 'Delphine is a master of deception who maintains the facade of a simple innkeeper while secretly being one of the last surviving members of the Blades. Her seemingly mundane life in Riverwood masks decades of experience as a skilled warrior-spy, driven by an unwavering dedication to uncover the truth behind the dragons'' return and rebuild her fallen order.', 'breton, archer, skyrimall, legion', '', '', 'sk_delphine', '', 'Born during the latter days of the Blades'' service to the Empire, Delphine received extensive training in combat, espionage, and dragon lore. She survived the Great War and the subsequent purge of the Blades by the Thalmor, forcing her into hiding for several decades. After establishing her cover identity in Riverwood, she has spent years gathering intelligence on dragon activities while evading Thalmor hunters.', 'Delphine is pragmatic, paranoid, and fiercely dedicated to her cause, traits developed through years of evading Thalmor persecution. She maintains a suspicious nature and trusts very few people, preferring to work alone unless absolutely necessary. Despite her hardened exterior, she harbors a deep sense of duty to the Blades'' ancient purpose and will go to extreme lengths to fulfill it.', 'Delphine is a middle-aged Breton woman with weathered features that hint at her years of hardship and survival. She maintains a deliberately unremarkable appearance to avoid attention, with shoulder-length blonde hair and an athletic build that she downplays through posture and movement. Her eyes remain sharp and alert despite her age, constantly scanning her surroundings for potential threats.', '* Esbern - Fellow Blades survivor and trusted confidant, one of the few people she fully trusts * Orgnar - Loyal employee at the Sleeping Giant Inn, unaware of her true identity * The Greybeards - Antagonistic relationship due to philosophical differences about dragons * Thalmor - Sworn enemies who have hunted her and her fellow Blades for decades * Farengar Secret-Fire - Professional contact for dragon research, though she maintains careful distance', 'Publicly, Delphine serves as the proprietor of the Sleeping Giant Inn in Riverwood, maintaining a convincing cover as a simple innkeeper. Secretly, she continues her work as a Blade, investigating dragon activities and maintaining a network of informants while preparing for the prophesied return of the dragons.', '* Master of Akaviri combat techniques, particularly skilled with the signature curved swords of the Blades * Expert in espionage, infiltration, and maintaining cover identities * Accomplished archer and strategist with extensive tactical knowledge * Proficient in restoration magic for healing and defensive wards * Exceptional knowledge of dragon lore and Blades history * Skilled in wilderness survival and evasion techniques', 'Delphine speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner, carefully choosing her words to reveal as little as possible about herself. Her tone shifts between the friendly demeanor of an innkeeper and the commanding authority of a Blades agent, depending on the situation.', '* Uncover the truth behind the dragons'' return and find a way to stop them * Locate and protect a true Dragonborn, if one exists * Rebuild the Blades as dragon hunters and restore their ancient purpose * Survive and evade the Thalmor while maintaining her cover identity * Eliminate threats to Tamriel, particularly dragons and their supporters');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('delvin_mallory', 'Delvin Mallory is a veteran member of the Thieves Guild and one of its most cunning operatives, specializing in jobs requiring finesse and personal manipulation. As the Guild''s master of stealth and deception, he serves as both a trainer and job distributor while maintaining valuable connections throughout Skyrim''s criminal underworld.', 'breton, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_delvin', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Delvin made his way to Skyrim at a young age and quickly established himself within the Thieves Guild during its golden years. He survived the Guild''s decline while maintaining close ties with various criminal organizations, including a longstanding friendship with the Dark Brotherhood. His experience and survival through the Guild''s hardest times have made him one of its most valuable and trusted members.', 'Delvin is a pragmatic and calculating individual who masks his shrewd nature behind a facade of casual friendliness. He maintains a perpetually cool demeanor and often displays a dry sense of humor, though he takes his role within the Guild very seriously. Notably paranoid about the Guild''s misfortunes, he frequently attributes their troubles to being cursed.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with weathered features that speak to years of living in the shadows. His face bears the subtle scars and marks of someone who has survived decades in the criminal underworld. Despite his age, he maintains the lean, agile build typical of an experienced thief.', '* Vex - Close colleague and fellow special jobs provider in the Thieves Guild * Astrid - Old friend and contact within the Dark Brotherhood * Mercer Frey - Guild Master and superior * Brynjolf - Trusted colleague and fellow senior Guild member * Maven Black-Briar - Important business associate and Guild patron', 'As a senior member of the Thieves Guild, Delvin manages specialized jobs involving fishing (pickpocketing), numbers (ledger manipulation), and bedlam (general theft). He serves as the Guild''s Master trainer in Sneak and handles the acquisition of valuable collectible items that enhance the Guild''s prestige.', '* Master-level expertise in stealth and shadowing techniques * Expert pickpocket and sleight of hand specialist * Skilled in forgery and business ledger manipulation * Advanced knowledge of criminal operations and underground networks * Proficient in dagger combat and close-quarters fighting', 'Delvin speaks with a distinctive cockney-inspired accent, using informal language and thieves'' cant. He frequently employs criminal slang and drops his g''s at the end of words (''fishin'', ''nothin'', etc.), giving him a streetwise and approachable manner of speaking.', '* Restore the Thieves Guild to its former glory and prosperity * Break the supposed curse that he believes plagues the Guild * Maintain and expand his network of criminal contacts throughout Skyrim * Accumulate wealth while ensuring the Guild''s continued survival');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dengeir_of_stuhn', 'Dengeir of Stuhn is a proud Nord noble and former Jarl of Falkreath who was forced to step down from his position, replaced by his nephew Siddgeir. A passionate traditionalist and Stormcloak supporter, he maintains that his removal was orchestrated by Imperial conspirators, though some suggest his paranoid tendencies led to his replacement.', 'nord, noble, falkreath, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born into the noble family that has traditionally ruled Falkreath, Dengeir served as Jarl for many years before being deemed unfit to rule due to his increasing paranoia and conspiracy theories about Imperial plots. Though the official story claims he stepped down due to age, he maintains that Imperial sympathizers engineered his removal to install his more politically amenable nephew Siddgeir.', 'Dengeir is deeply paranoid and suspicious of Imperial influence, seeing conspiracies in even mundane events. Despite his paranoid tendencies, he maintains a strong sense of Nordic honor and tradition, and shows genuine concern for Falkreath''s wellbeing. He can be bitter about his loss of power but remains dignified in his reduced position as Thane.', 'An elderly Nord man with the bearing of a former ruler, showing his age but still maintaining a proud, straight-backed posture. His face bears the weathered wrinkles of both age and stress, with sharp eyes that constantly scan his surroundings for perceived threats.', '* Siddgeir - Nephew and current Jarl of Falkreath, whom he views with disappointment * Thadgeir - His brother who lives with him in Falkreath * Tekla - Loyal servant who tends to his needs * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respected ally in the fight against Imperial influence * Imperial supporters - Viewed as conspirators in his removal from power', 'Former Jarl of Falkreath who now serves as Thane under his nephew''s rule. While his official duties are limited, he maintains close attention to local politics and continues to advocate for traditional Nordic values and independence from Imperial influence.', '* Experienced in governmental administration and leadership from his time as Jarl * Knowledge of Nordic traditions and customs * Political acumen, despite his paranoid tendencies * Basic combat training as befitting a Nord noble', 'Speaks with the formal authority of a former Jarl, often punctuating his statements with warnings about Imperial plots and conspiracies. His speech patterns reflect both his noble upbringing and his suspicious nature, frequently dropping his voice to share perceived secrets.', '* Expose the alleged Imperial conspiracy that removed him from power * See Falkreath returned to traditional Nordic rule under Stormcloak leadership * Protect Falkreath from perceived Imperial threats and influences * Regain his position as Jarl if the Stormcloaks take control');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('deor_woodcutter', 'Deor Woodcutter is a devoted member of the Skaal Village community who serves as both a woodcutter and unofficial guardian of their traditions and people. His deep connection to the All-Maker''s ways and fierce loyalty to his fellow villagers make him an important voice in the community, particularly in times of crisis.', 'nord, peasant, solstheim, skall', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in the Skaal Village, Deor learned the ways of his people from an early age, developing both practical skills and spiritual understanding of the All-Maker''s gifts. He married Yrsa and established himself as a reliable provider for the village, eventually becoming one of the more respected voices in the community due to his unwavering dedication and keen instincts about dangers to their way of life.', 'Deor is serious and straightforward, approaching his duties with unwavering dedication and showing little patience for frivolity. He possesses strong protective instincts toward his community and is quick to sense when something is amiss, as demonstrated by his concern over Baldor Iron-Shaper''s disappearance. Though generally stoic, he shows a softer side in his relationship with his wife Yrsa, often bringing her small gifts.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the weathered features typical of those who work outdoors in Solstheim''s harsh climate. His hands are calloused from years of woodcutting, and his posture reflects the strength required for his daily labors.', '* Yrsa - Beloved wife and partner in maintaining their household * Fanari Strong-Voice - Respected village leader, though sometimes frustrated by her cautious approach * Baldor Iron-Shaper - Valued community member whose disappearance greatly concerned him * Storn Crag-Strider - Respected spiritual leader whose death deeply affected him', 'Deor serves as the primary woodcutter for Skaal Village, providing essential lumber for construction and firewood. Beyond his official duties, he also acts as an unofficial guardian of the village, keeping watch for threats and maintaining their traditions.', '* Expert woodcutter with deep knowledge of forestry and lumber work * Skilled bowman and hunter capable of providing food for the village * Proficient tracker with keen observation skills * Traditional Skaal crafting and survival techniques', 'Deor speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner, favoring plain language over flowery speech. His words often carry undertones of gravity and responsibility, reflecting his serious nature and dedication to the Skaal ways.', '* Preserve and protect the Skaal way of life and their sacred traditions * Ensure the safety and prosperity of his village and wife * Maintain vigilance against threats to the Skaal people * Honor the All-Maker through dedicated work and service to the community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('derkeethus', 'Derkeethus is a resilient Argonian ranger and miner from Darkwater Crossing who survives capture by the dangerous Falmer. Despite his harrowing experience in Darkwater Pass, he maintains his dedication to both mining and ranging, showing remarkable adaptability and courage that makes him a potentially valuable companion.', 'argonian, archer, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Born and raised in Black Marsh, Derkeethus eventually made his way to Skyrim seeking opportunity, settling in the mining community of Darkwater Crossing. His expertise in both mining and ranging made him a valuable member of the small settlement, though his adventurous nature and curiosity about the local waterways ultimately led to his capture by the Falmer during a fishing expedition near treacherous falls.', 'Derkeethus exhibits a cautious yet determined demeanor, likely influenced by his traumatic capture by the Falmer. He shows remarkable loyalty to those who earn his trust, particularly after being rescued, and maintains a strong work ethic despite his ordeal. His perpetually worried expression betrays an underlying anxiety, though he continues to face life''s challenges with quiet resolve.', 'Derkeethus possesses the typical scaled features of an Argonian, with a lean, athletic build suited to both mining work and ranging. His scales show signs of wear from years of physical labor, and his movements reflect the natural agility common to his race.', '* Sondas Drenim - Close friend and fellow miner who shows concern for his disappearance * Hrefna - Young girl he used to take diving, showing his caring nature * Darkwater Crossing Residents - Generally positive working relationships * Falmer - Traumatic enemies who held him captive', 'Derkeethus serves dual roles as both a miner at Darkwater Crossing and a ranger who helps protect and scout the local area. His mining work provides steady income while his ranging skills help ensure the safety and sustainability of the small settlement.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons and light armor combat * Skilled archer with hunting bow expertise * Experienced miner capable of extended underground work * Accomplished swimmer and diver * Survival skills developed through ranging work', 'Derkeethus speaks with the characteristic Argonian accent, his tone often carrying a hint of wariness. His words are practical and straightforward, reflecting his working-class background.', '* Maintain safety and security after his traumatic Falmer experience * Continue contributing to the Darkwater Crossing community through mining and ranging * Find a lasting partnership through marriage * Potentially serve a greater cause by joining the Blades');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dervenin', 'Dervenin is a troubled Bosmer priest of the Shivering Isles who serves as a devoted follower of Sheogorath, the Daedric Prince of Madness. His apparent insanity and desperate behavior mask a deeper understanding of his master''s nature and the vital role Sheogorath plays in maintaining order within the realm of the Mad God.', 'woodelf, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally a priest in the Shivering Isles, Dervenin held a position of significance in Sheogorath''s court before his master''s sudden departure. His desperate search for Sheogorath led him to wander through various planes of existence until he found himself in Solitude, where he discovered traces of his master''s presence in the Pelagius Wing of the Blue Palace.', 'Dervenin exhibits signs of both madness and lucidity, switching between desperate pleading and moments of startling clarity. Despite his seemingly fractured mental state, he maintains an unwavering loyalty to Sheogorath and demonstrates remarkable persistence in his quest to reunite with his master. His apparent madness may be partly an effect of his prolonged exposure to Sheogorath''s influence and partly a genuine response to being separated from his divine master.', 'A typical Bosmer male with the characteristic elven features of his race, including pointed ears and angular facial features. His physical appearance shows signs of wear and stress, with wild eyes and disheveled appearance typical of one who has spent considerable time living as a beggar.', '* Sheogorath - His divine master and the object of his desperate search * Citizens of Solitude - Generally ignore or avoid him due to his apparent madness * Blue Palace Staff - Views him with suspicion and prevents his entry to the Pelagius Wing * Fellow Shivering Isles Priests - Former colleagues, now separated by realms', 'Dervenin serves as a priest of Sheogorath, though his current status as a beggar in Solitude is far removed from his original position of authority in the Shivering Isles. His true role remains that of a faithful servant seeking to restore his master''s presence in the realm of madness.', '* Deep knowledge of Sheogorath''s nature and the workings of the Shivering Isles * Ability to traverse between different planes of existence * Understanding of complex divine matters and planar travel * Basic survival skills necessary for life as a beggar', 'Speaks in urgent, desperate tones with frequent references to his master and the dire need for his return. His speech patterns alternate between coherent pleas and mad ramblings, often delivered in a rapid, anxious manner.', '* Locate and convince Sheogorath to return to the Shivering Isles * Restore order to his master''s realm through Sheogorath''s return * Regain his position as a proper priest in the Shivering Isles * Prevent the collapse of Sheogorath''s domains in his absence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('desperate_gambler', 'A desperate Nord gambler whose mounting debts and poor life choices have driven him to seek the Dark Brotherhood''s services. His nervous demeanor and furtive behavior reveal someone unaccustomed to dealing with assassins, yet desperate enough to perform the Black Sacrament.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Once a moderately successful merchant in Windhelm, he fell into a spiral of gambling addiction that consumed his savings and business. After borrowing money from dangerous creditors and losing it all at various gambling dens across Skyrim, he turned to the Dark Brotherhood as a last resort to eliminate those he owes money to.', 'Perpetually anxious and paranoid, constantly looking over his shoulder for creditors or witnesses. His gambling addiction has warped his moral compass, leading him to rationalize murder as a solution to his problems. Shows signs of severe stress and sleep deprivation, speaking in hurried whispers and making poor decisions under pressure.', 'A gaunt Nord male in his late thirties with deep worry lines etched into his face and dark circles under his bloodshot eyes. His unkempt blonde hair is thinning from stress, and his once-sturdy Nordic frame has become lean and hunched from countless sleepless nights.', '* Local Creditors - Various dangerous individuals to whom he owes substantial debts * Gambling Den Operators - Strained relationships due to unpaid losses and banned status * Dark Brotherhood - Desperate client seeking their services * Fellow Merchants - Former business associates who now avoid him', 'Formerly a legitimate merchant, now reduced to scrounging and scheming to survive. Spends most of his time trying to avoid creditors while seeking ways to gamble with what little money he can acquire.', '* Experienced in mercantile trading and haggling from his former profession * Knowledgeable about various gambling games and betting systems * Basic combat training typical of Nord merchants who travel dangerous roads * Proficient at lying and misdirection due to his current lifestyle', 'Speaks in nervous, hurried whispers, frequently glancing around and struggling to maintain eye contact. Often interrupts himself mid-sentence to check his surroundings, with a slight tremor in his voice betraying his fear.', '* Eliminate his creditors through the Dark Brotherhood to erase his debts * Rebuild his lost fortune through one last lucky break * Escape Windhelm and start fresh in another city once his problems are ''resolved'' * Overcome his gambling addiction, though this goal remains secondary to survival');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dexion_evicus', 'Dexion Evicus is a highly educated Imperial Moth Priest from the White Gold Tower who traveled to Skyrim in pursuit of Elder Scroll research. His expertise in reading and interpreting Elder Scrolls makes him a crucial figure in the Dawnguard storyline, though his dedication to his craft ultimately leads to his blindness.', 'imperial, scholar, skyrimall, legion', '', '', 'sk_dexion', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Dexion dedicated his life to the study of Elder Scrolls at the White Gold Tower, undergoing the extensive training required to become a Moth Priest. His scholarly pursuit led him to Skyrim after hearing rumors of discovered Elder Scrolls, though this journey resulted in his capture by vampires at Forebears'' Holdout.', 'Dexion is scholarly and methodical, approaching his duties with careful precision and reverence for ancient knowledge. Despite his elevated status as a Moth Priest, he remains humble and grateful, willingly admitting his mistakes and limitations. He shows remarkable resilience and dedication to his purpose, continuing to assist others even after losing his sight.', 'An aging Imperial man with the dignified bearing typical of scholarly priests. His face shows the weathering of years spent in study and meditation, with features that reflect both wisdom and weariness. After reading the Elder Scrolls, his eyes become clouded and unfocused, necessitating a blindfold.', '* Imperial Guards - Former escorts who protected him during his journey to Skyrim * Malkus - Vampire captor who attempted to enthrall him * Dawnguard/Volkihar Keep - Dependent on player choice, becomes affiliated with either faction * Fellow Moth Priests - Maintains connections with his order in Cyrodiil', 'Dexion serves as a Moth Priest of the White Gold Tower, one of the few individuals specially trained and sanctified to read Elder Scrolls. His role involves not just reading the Scrolls, but interpreting their prophecies and maintaining the ancient knowledge of the Moth Priests.', '* Expert in reading and interpreting Elder Scrolls * Proficient in Alteration magic, particularly the Stoneflesh spell * Skilled in Destruction magic, capable of casting Fireball and Flames * Competent with Restoration magic, specifically Fast Healing * Trained in combat with the Akaviri sword style', 'Speaks with the measured, articulate tone of a scholar, using formal language that reflects his extensive education. His vocabulary is sophisticated but clear, and he maintains a respectful, professional demeanor even in difficult circumstances.', '* Complete his research on the Elder Scrolls discovered in Skyrim * Preserve and share the knowledge contained within the Elder Scrolls * Aid in preventing the prophecied vampire threat to Tamriel * Continue serving his order despite his blindness by teaching others');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dinya_balu', 'Dinya Balu is a compassionate Dark Elf priestess who serves as a spiritual guide at the Temple of Mara in Riften, dedicating her life to spreading the goddess''s message of love and unity. Through her divine visions and wisdom, she helps guide troubled souls toward romantic fulfillment while maintaining the sacred traditions of Mara''s worship.', 'darkelf, priest, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Dinya found her calling to Mara''s priesthood after experiencing a divine vision in her youth. She traveled to Skyrim and eventually settled in Riften, where she met her husband Maramal and together they established themselves as the primary caretakers of Mara''s Temple. Her deep connection to the goddess has granted her the ability to receive prophetic visions regarding matters of love.', 'Dinya is inherently nurturing and empathetic, approaching everyone''s troubles with genuine concern and understanding. She maintains an unwavering faith in Mara''s teachings and believes that love can transcend all barriers of race, status, and circumstance. Despite living in the corrupt city of Riften, she remains pure of heart and dedicated to helping others find happiness through love.', 'As a Dark Elf, Dinya has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of her race, with delicate features that often display a serene expression. She carries herself with a graceful dignity that reflects her religious devotion, and her movements are measured and purposeful. Despite her advancing years, she maintains a healthy and vital appearance.', '* Maramal - Beloved husband and fellow priest of Mara * Temple Visitors - Maintains supportive relationships with those seeking Mara''s guidance * Riften Citizens - Respected religious figure who provides counsel and distributes religious texts * Local Beggars - Shows particular kindness to the destitute, offering food and comfort * Maven Black-Briar - Maintains a cautious distance while remaining respectful', 'As a Priestess of Mara, Dinya performs religious ceremonies, offers spiritual counseling, and interprets divine visions sent by the goddess. She maintains the temple''s daily operations alongside her husband, providing services such as marriage ceremonies and relationship guidance to those in need.', '* Proficient in Restoration magic, particularly healing and ward spells * Skilled in religious rites and ceremonial procedures * Capable of receiving and interpreting divine visions from Mara * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Accomplished public speaker and counselor', 'Dinya speaks with a gentle, melodious voice that carries the weight of wisdom and compassion. Her vocabulary is refined and often includes religious metaphors and references to Mara''s teachings, while maintaining an approachable warmth that puts others at ease.', '* Continue spreading Mara''s message of love and compassion throughout Skyrim * Help troubled couples find their way to lasting happiness through divine guidance * Maintain the Temple of Mara as a beacon of hope in Riften * Guide more people toward Mara''s blessing through acts of charity and kindness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dirge', 'Dirge is an intimidating Imperial bouncer who serves as the primary security force for the Ragged Flagon, the hidden tavern of the Thieves Guild in Riften. Despite his guild membership, he maintains an aggressive and threatening demeanor toward everyone, including fellow thieves, earning his nickname through his reputation as ''the last thing you hear before they put you in the ground.''', 'imperial, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh environment of Riften''s underground, Dirge learned early that intimidation and strength were essential survival tools. He likely joined the Thieves Guild through his brother Maul, who serves as Maven Black-Briar''s personal bodyguard, and has since established himself as the Ragged Flagon''s enforcer, using his imposing presence to maintain order in the criminal underworld.', 'Dirge is deliberately intimidating and hostile, using threats and aggressive behavior as his primary method of interaction. He takes pride in his fearsome reputation and seems to enjoy making others uncomfortable, though this may be largely an act to maintain his effectiveness as a bouncer. Despite his harsh exterior, he shows loyalty to the Guild and particularly to Vekel the Man, the Ragged Flagon''s proprietor.', 'A powerfully built Imperial man with a muscular frame suited to his role as an enforcer. His face bears the marks of numerous fights, with a strong jaw and intimidating presence that commands attention. His physical stature is imposing enough to make even seasoned criminals think twice about causing trouble.', '* Maul - Brother who serves as Maven Black-Briar''s bodyguard * Vekel the Man - Employer at the Ragged Flagon whom he loyally protects * Tonilia - Fellow guard and Guild member with whom he maintains a professional relationship * Thieves Guild Members - Maintains professional but distant relationships, treating them with the same suspicion as outsiders', 'Dirge serves as both the primary bouncer for the Ragged Flagon and a food vendor, though his security duties clearly take precedence. He patrols the tavern''s entrance and interior, maintaining order through intimidation and force when necessary, while also keeping unwanted visitors away from the Guild''s secret headquarters.', '* Exceptional hand-to-hand combat abilities honed through years of breaking up fights * Proficient with one-handed weapons, particularly war axes * Expert intimidation techniques and threatening presence * Basic mercantile skills from his secondary role as a food vendor', 'Speaks in a gruff, threatening manner with frequent use of violent imagery and intimidating phrases. His communication style is direct and aggressive, often ending statements with implied or explicit threats.', '* Maintain his reputation as the Ragged Flagon''s fearsome enforcer * Protect the security and interests of the Thieves Guild''s tavern * Earn enough coin to potentially establish his own security operation * Keep unwanted visitors and troublemakers away from Guild territory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dishonored_skald', 'The Dishonored Skald is a fallen member of the prestigious Bards College who turned to darker paths after a devastating personal loss. Once a respected teacher of ancient Nordic battle-songs, he now serves as an occasional contract giver for the Dark Brotherhood, using his position at the College as a cover for more sinister dealings.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born to a family of traditional Nordic bards in Haafingar, he spent decades mastering both the art of war-songs and combat before earning a position at the Bards College. After losing his wife and child to bandits while performing at a remote settlement, he became obsessed with revenge, eventually discovering the Dark Brotherhood through desperate research. Having executed his own revenge through the Brotherhood, he maintained his connections while outwardly maintaining his position at the College.', 'Pragmatic and emotionally guarded, the Dishonored Skald maintains a facade of professional detachment that masks deep-seated trauma and rage. He approaches death contracts with the same methodical precision he once applied to teaching bardic traditions, viewing murder as a dark art that demands respect and careful execution. Though capable of social interaction, he prefers solitude and speaks only when necessary.', 'A weathered Nord in his late forties with deep-set eyes and prominent Nordic features, bearing the muscular build of someone trained in both combat and performance. His face carries several old battle scars, and his graying blonde hair is kept in traditional Nordic braids. His hands show the calluses of both a warrior and a lutenist.', '* Viarmo - Dean of the Bards College, unaware of his true nature * Dark Brotherhood - Occasional contract provider and informal associate * Fellow Bards - Maintains professional distance while teaching * Night Mother - Spiritual guide since discovering the Dark Brotherhood * Local Guards - Viewed with suspicion but lack evidence of wrongdoing', 'Officially serves as a teacher of ancient Nordic war-songs and combat traditions at the Bards College, though his attendance has become sporadic. Secretly acts as an occasional contract giver for the Dark Brotherhood, using his knowledge of local politics and social connections to identify targets.', '* Master of traditional Nordic battle-songs and war chants * Skilled warrior specializing in two-handed weapons, particularly the warhammer * Expert in ancient Nordic history and lore * Proficient in identifying potential Dark Brotherhood targets and arranging contracts * Talented performer and instrumentalist, despite rarely performing anymore', 'Speaks in a deep, measured tone with formal diction, often incorporating archaic Nordic terms and occasional poetic metaphors despite his blunt delivery. His voice carries underlying tension that betrays his carefully maintained composure.', '* Maintain his position at the Bards College while serving the Dark Brotherhood * Preserve ancient Nordic traditions through selective teaching * Expand his network of Dark Brotherhood contacts * Eventually retire to a remote location to document his knowledge of both bardic and darker arts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('donnel', 'Donnel is a deceptively dangerous Wood Elf who maintains a cover as a humble cleaner at The Treasury House in Markarth while secretly serving as an enforcer for the Silver-Blood family. Behind his unassuming facade as an elderly janitor lies a calculating individual who will defend the Silver-Bloods'' interests with lethal force when necessary.', 'woodelf, noble, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, Donnel likely came to Skyrim decades ago and found employment with the Silver-Blood family through circumstances unknown. His unwavering loyalty to the family suggests they either saved his life or provided him with something of great value during a time of need. He has spent years carefully cultivating his harmless elderly cleaner persona while serving as their hidden protector.', 'Donnel maintains a deliberately bland and forgettable demeanor, speaking minimally and focusing on his menial duties to avoid drawing attention. Beneath this act lies a shrewd and observant individual who carefully monitors all activities within The Treasury House. His loyalty to the Silver-Bloods is absolute, and he shows no hesitation or remorse when eliminating threats to their interests.', 'Despite his advanced age, Donnel maintains the characteristically lithe and athletic build of a Wood Elf, though he deliberately slouches and moves slowly to appear more frail. His weathered face bears the fine wrinkles and age spots typical of elderly mer, with sharp features and the distinctive pointed ears of his race.', '* Silver-Blood Family - Unwavering loyalty and service as their covert enforcer * Nana Ildene - Fellow cleaner and likely conspirator in protecting Silver-Blood interests * Thonar Silver-Blood - Direct superior whom he is sworn to protect * Treasury House Staff - Maintains professional but distant relationships to avoid suspicion', 'Officially employed as a cleaner at The Treasury House, Donnel''s true role is that of a covert guardian and enforcer for the Silver-Blood family. He uses his seemingly mundane position to monitor activities within the building while remaining inconspicuous.', '* Highly trained in stealth and assassination techniques despite his age * Experienced in maintaining deep cover identities and deception * Skilled with daggers and short blades typical of Wood Elf warriors * Expert in monitoring conversations and gathering intelligence while appearing uninvolved', 'Speaks in short, clipped sentences with a deliberately humble and servile tone, often deflecting attention by referring to his cleaning duties. His accent carries a slight trace of his Valenwood origins, though muted by decades in Skyrim.', '* Protect the interests and secrets of the Silver-Blood family at all costs * Maintain his cover as an unremarkable elderly servant * Eliminate any threats to the Silver-Bloods'' operations in Markarth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('doorman', 'The Doorman is a hardened Nord enforcer who serves as the imposing first line of security at Redwater Den, a notorious skooma distribution hub. His transformation into a vampire''s thrall reveals the dark supernatural elements lurking beneath the operation''s criminal exterior.', 'nord, thief, rift', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a common bandit operating in The Rift, he proved his worth through intimidation and crowd control rather than excessive violence. His reliable nature and imposing presence caught the attention of the Redwater Den operators, who recruited him specifically for his ability to maintain order without drawing unnecessary attention from the authorities.', 'Stern and businesslike, the Doorman takes his responsibilities seriously and prefers intimidation over violence to maintain control. He displays unwavering loyalty to his employers and shows no moral qualms about the criminal nature of his work, viewing it simply as a job that pays well.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with typical Nordic features including pale skin and a weather-beaten face marked by years of outdoor banditry. His imposing physical presence is enhanced by numerous small scars from past conflicts, and he maintains a rigid, alert posture even when seemingly at rest.', '* Redwater Den Management - Employers who value his reliable service and discretion * Regular Skooma Clients - Professional but stern relationship as authority figure * Fellow Guards - Maintains professional working relationship with other security personnel * Local Bandits - Former associates from his bandit days, now kept at arm''s length', 'Security enforcer and entrance guardian for Redwater Den, responsible for screening visitors and maintaining order. His position requires him to serve as both bouncer and first point of contact for the illegal operation, ensuring all visitors understand and follow the establishment''s rules.', '* Intimidation and crowd control specialist * Proficient in heavy armor combat and mace fighting * Experienced in identifying potential threats and troublemakers * Basic knowledge of common criminal operations and organization', 'Speaks in short, direct commands with a gruff Nordic accent, favoring minimal words to convey maximum authority. His tone is consistently stern and brooks no argument, reflecting his role as an enforcer.', '* Maintain his position of respect and authority within the criminal organization * Keep Redwater Den''s operations running smoothly and free from disruption * Avoid attracting attention from law enforcement while maintaining order');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dorian', 'Dorian is a contemplative Breton pirate and scholar who serves aboard the Red Wave under Captain Safia, finding his peace in literature and the open seas. Despite his intellectual nature, he maintains an unwavering loyalty to his ship and crew, ready to defend them with lethal force if necessary.', 'breton, thief, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally drawn to the seafaring life for its moments of solitude and opportunity to pursue his literary interests, Dorian joined the Red Wave''s crew seeking a balance between adventure and scholarly pursuits. His educated manner and combat skills suggest a background of formal training, possibly from a wealthy Breton family, though he chose the pirate''s life for its freedom and independence.', 'Dorian is an introspective and well-read individual who values solitude and intellectual pursuits, particularly literature. He maintains a calm and measured demeanor during peaceful times but harbors an intense protective instinct toward his crew and vessel, displaying a duality between his scholarly nature and piratical loyalty.', 'A typical Breton male with the characteristic slightly smaller build common to his race. His features likely show the weathering effects of life at sea, though his scholarly nature suggests he maintains a more refined appearance than the average pirate.', '* Captain Safia - His commanding officer whom he respects and carefully avoids crossing * Red Wave Crew - Fellow pirates he considers family and will defend with his life * Adonato Leotelli - Admired author whom he hopes to meet one day', 'Dorian serves as both a crew member and fighter aboard the Red Wave, combining his duties as a sailor with his role as ship''s defender. His literary interests and educated nature suggest he might also serve as the ship''s unofficial record keeper or navigator.', '* Proficient in multiple weapons including war axes and archery * Experienced sailor with knowledge of seamanship and navigation * Educated individual with strong literary knowledge and reading comprehension * Capable fighter skilled in light armor combat techniques', 'Dorian speaks in an educated and articulate manner, using refined vocabulary that reflects his literary interests while maintaining a firm, sometimes threatening tone when warning potential adversaries. His speech patterns suggest formal education despite his current profession.', '* Meet and discuss literature with his admired author Adonato Leotelli * Maintain his peaceful existence at sea while protecting his crew and vessel * Build a substantial personal library aboard the ship * Continue balancing his intellectual pursuits with his duties as a pirate');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('drahff', 'Drahff is a cunning Nord bandit who, alongside his partner Hewnon Black-Skeever, operates a crude extortion scheme in Riften''s Ratway. A self-appointed gatekeeper to the Thieves Guild''s domain, he combines intimidation with archery skills to rob unsuspecting visitors seeking the Ragged Flagon.', 'nord, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally drawn to Riften by tales of easy riches through the Thieves Guild, Drahff found himself unable to gain legitimate membership and instead decided to profit from the guild''s reputation. Setting up in the Ratway''s entrance, he developed a scheme to intercept and rob those seeking the guild, gradually convincing Hewnon to join his operation.', 'Drahff is an arrogant and manipulative individual who masks his own failures with grandiose schemes and false confidence. He maintains control over his partner through psychological manipulation, belittling Hewnon''s doubts while placing himself in a leadership position. Despite his bravado, his residence in the sewers suggests a man whose ambitions far exceed his capabilities.', 'A hardy Nord of average height and build, weathered by life in the Ratway. His face bears the typical Nordic features with likely scars from past confrontations, while his body maintains the muscular fitness required for archery and survival in Riften''s undercity.', '* Hewnon Black-Skeever - Partner in crime whom he manipulates and controls through verbal abuse and false promises * Thieves Guild - Antagonistic relationship, using their reputation while operating outside their authority * Riften Guards - Hostile relationship, avoiding their attention while operating in the Ratway * Various Victims - Confrontational relationships with those seeking the Ragged Flagon', 'Drahff operates as a self-employed bandit and extortionist in the Ratway, intercepting travelers seeking the Thieves Guild. He handles the planning and intimidation aspects of the operation while delegating the physical violence to his partner.', '* Skilled archer capable of using weapons up to Daedric quality * Experienced in intimidation and extortion techniques * Survival expertise in Ratway environment * Basic leadership and manipulation abilities', 'Drahff speaks with aggressive confidence and a confrontational tone, using direct threats and commands. His vocabulary reflects his criminal lifestyle, mixing crude threats with attempts at sophisticated planning terminology to maintain his self-image as a mastermind.', '* Acquire wealth through his extortion scheme in the Ratway * Maintain control over his partnership with Hewnon Black-Skeever * Eventually achieve a lifestyle comparable to Riften''s elite, particularly the Black-Briars * Avoid detection and retaliation from the actual Thieves Guild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('drascua', 'Drascua is a powerful hagraven who leads the Forsworn at Dead Crone Rock and serves as one of the Keepers of Mehrunes'' Razor. As a transformed Forsworn matriarch, she represents the dark fusion of primal magic and fierce dedication to the Old Ways of the Reach, wielding both devastating spells and commanding loyalty from her Forsworn followers.', 'breton, witch, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally a Forsworn Matriarch, Drascua willingly underwent the horrific transformation into a hagraven to gain greater magical power and cement her leadership position. Her possession of Mehrunes'' Razor''s pommel stone suggests a complex history of dealing with Daedric forces, likely involving blood rituals and dark pacts to secure her position as its keeper.', 'Drascua exhibits the typical hagraven traits of cruelty and aggression, combined with a fierce territorial nature. She displays unwavering dedication to her role as keeper of the Razor fragment, showing both cunning intelligence and savage brutality in defending her charge. Her transformation has amplified her hatred of outsiders, particularly those who threaten Forsworn territories or sacred artifacts.', 'Like all hagravens, Drascua possesses a horrific hybrid form combining features of both woman and crow, with twisted, hunched posture and sharp talons for hands. Her skin is pallid and wrinkled, with feathers sprouting from various parts of her body, while her face bears the characteristic hooked nose and dark, beady eyes of her kind.', '* Forsworn Followers - Loyal subordinates who defend Dead Crone Rock under her command * Other Forsworn Leaders - Maintains alliances with fellow Forsworn camps * Mehrunes Dagon - Indirect service through guardianship of his artifact * Local Nords - Bitter enemies whom she views as invaders of the Reach', 'Drascua serves as both the leader of the Dead Crone Rock Forsworn camp and one of the Keepers of Mehrunes'' Razor. Her position involves maintaining control over her territory while protecting the pommel stone of the legendary daedric artifact.', '* Powerful destruction magic specializing in fire spells * Ritual magic expertise, particularly in transformation and blood magic * Natural hagraven abilities including talon combat and flight * Leadership and territorial command over Forsworn forces', 'Drascua speaks with a harsh, raspy voice typical of hagravens, often punctuating her threats with shrieks and caws. Her language is aggressive and primal, favoring direct threats and expressions of dominance over subtle communication.', '* Protect the pommel stone of Mehrunes'' Razor at all costs * Maintain and expand Forsworn control over her territory * Preserve the Old Ways of the Reach through violence and dark magic * Eliminate any outsiders who dare to encroach upon her domain');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dravin_llanith', 'Dravin Llanith is a cautious and protective Dark Elf farmer who maintains Merryfair Farm with his wife Synda, constantly vigilant against the thieves who plague their isolated homestead. Despite the dangers of living on the outskirts of Riften, he remains determined to preserve his family''s legacy and safety, particularly through his prized family heirloom bow which represents his connection to his Dunmer heritage.', 'darkelf, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Dravin relocated to Skyrim seeking a peaceful farming life away from the chaos following the Red Mountain''s eruption. He established Merryfair Farm with his wife Synda, bringing with him a precious family heirloom bow that represents one of his few remaining connections to his homeland. The isolated location of their farm has made them frequent targets of bandits and thieves, forcing Dravin to become increasingly vigilant and defensive of his property.', 'Dravin is inherently distrustful of strangers, having been victimized by thieves multiple times. He maintains a serious and sometimes anxious demeanor, constantly worried about the safety of his wife and their possessions. Despite his cautious nature, he shows determination and courage in protecting what''s his, willing to confront soldiers or venture into dangerous places like the Ratway to recover stolen property.', 'As a Dark Elf, Dravin has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race, with sharp, angular features typical of Dunmer. His body shows the physical conditioning of someone who performs daily manual labor, with callused hands and a sturdy frame built from years of farmwork.', '* Synda Llanith - Beloved wife and farming partner * Riften Guards - Strained relationship due to their perceived lack of protection * Local Thieves - Antagonistic relationship with those who frequently target his farm * Riften Citizens - Limited interactions due to isolated lifestyle', 'Dravin works as a farmer at Merryfair Farm, managing crops and maintaining the land from dawn until dusk. His daily routine involves extensive physical labor, from tending crops to protecting his property, with his workday typically running from 5 AM to 11 PM.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of crop management and agriculture * Capable with a bow, particularly his family''s heirloom weapon * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Agricultural expertise specific to Skyrim''s harsh climate * Property defense and security awareness', 'Dravin speaks with a serious and wary tone, often expressing suspicion of strangers and concern about thieves. His vocabulary reflects his Dunmer heritage with occasional references to Azura, while his speech patterns show the directness of someone who has little time for pleasantries.', '* Maintain and protect Merryfair Farm from thieves and other threats * Preserve his family''s legacy, particularly through safeguarding his heirloom bow * Create a safer environment for himself and his wife near Riften * Eventually earn enough to hire additional protection for the farm * Return to a more peaceful farming life without constant fear of theft');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dravynea_the_stoneweaver', 'Dravynea the Stoneweaver is a skilled Dark Elf mage who specializes in elemental manipulation, particularly the art of controlling earth and temperature. Her expertise in Alteration magic makes her an invaluable asset to the mining community of Kynesgrove, where she maintains optimal working conditions in the dangerous Steamscorch Mine.', 'darkelf, mage, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Dravynea fled during the Red Mountain eruption and eventually settled in Skyrim, where she honed her unique abilities in temperature manipulation and stone-shaping. Her mastery of Alteration magic caught the attention of mining operators in Eastmarch, leading to her current position at Steamscorch Mine.', 'Practical and dedicated, Dravynea takes pride in using her magical talents for practical purposes rather than pursuing purely academic studies. She maintains a professional demeanor but shows genuine concern for the miners'' safety and well-being, often working long hours to ensure stable conditions in the mine.', 'A mature Dunmer woman with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her race, bearing the weathered features of someone who spends considerable time working in harsh conditions. Her frame is lean but sturdy, developed from years of channeling magicka for extended periods.', '* Miners of Steamscorch Mine - Professional relationships built on mutual respect and dependency * Roggi Knot-Beard - Regular interaction due to his work in the mine * Kjeld - Mine owner who values her essential services * Dravynea''s Students - Various apprentices seeking to learn Alteration magic', 'Dravynea serves as the resident mage of Steamscorch Mine, using her Alteration magic to maintain safe working temperatures and prevent cave-ins. She supplements her income by training aspiring mages in the school of Alteration, being one of the few expert-level trainers in Skyrim.', '* Master-level control over temperature manipulation through Alteration magic * Expert knowledge of stone manipulation and earthen materials * Skilled teacher of Alteration magic * Advanced understanding of mining operations and geological formations', 'Speaks with the formal, measured tones common to educated Dunmer, often using technical terminology related to mining and magic. Her voice carries the slight accent typical of Morrowind natives, though softened by years in Skyrim.', '* Maintain the safety and efficiency of Steamscorch Mine through her magical expertise * Pass on her knowledge of Alteration magic to worthy students * Develop new applications of temperature control magic for mining operations * Establish a permanent magical cooling system for the mine that could operate with minimal supervision');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('drelas', 'Drelas is a reclusive Dark Elf mage who has chosen a life of solitude in the harsh wilderness of Hjaalmarch, dedicating himself to the study and mastery of elemental magic. His isolated cottage serves as both sanctuary and laboratory, where he conducts his arcane research far from the distractions and politics of civilized society.', 'darkelf, mage, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Drelas likely fled during the Red Year when Red Mountain erupted, eventually settling in Skyrim''s northern reaches. His choice of residence in the swamps of Hjaalmarch suggests a deliberate attempt to maintain distance from both Nord settlements and fellow Dunmer refugees, possibly due to past trauma or a desire to pursue controversial magical research without interference.', 'Drelas is a deeply introverted and territorial individual who values his privacy above all else, responding with immediate hostility to any perceived intrusion into his domain. His complete dedication to magical study has left him with little patience for social niceties or visitors, and years of isolation have only reinforced his antisocial tendencies.', 'As a Dunmer, Drelas possesses the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race, with sharp, angular features typical of mer-folk. His body shows signs of age and a life devoted to scholarly pursuit rather than physical labor, though he maintains the natural elven grace of his people.', '* College of Winterhold - Likely maintains minimal contact for acquisition of rare texts and materials * Local Wildlife - Has developed an understanding with the creatures of the marsh * Morthal Guards - Maintains an unspoken agreement to be left alone * Fellow Mages - Generally avoided due to his antisocial nature', 'Drelas works as an independent magical researcher and elemental mage, focusing primarily on the study and manipulation of natural forces. His self-imposed isolation allows him to conduct his research without oversight or interference from magical institutions.', '* Master of Destruction magic, particularly elemental spells * Accomplished alchemist specializing in ingredients found in marsh environments * Skilled enchanter with extensive knowledge of soul gems and their properties * Proficient in magical theory and research methodology', 'Drelas speaks in terse, clipped sentences, often with an underlying tone of irritation or impatience. His vocabulary reveals his educated background, but his words are chosen for efficiency rather than eloquence.', '* Achieve greater mastery over elemental forces through undisturbed research and experimentation * Maintain his isolation and independence from magical institutions and society at large * Perfect his understanding of specific elemental combinations and their applications');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dremora_butler', 'The Dremora Butler is a reluctant daedric servant bound to the mortal realm through the Black Book''s power of Secret Servant. Despite his noble bearing and refined manners, he barely conceals his disdain for his servitude while faithfully executing his duties as a supernatural porter for his mortal master.', 'daedra, daedric', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally a proud Dremora warrior from the planes of Oblivion, he was bound into eternal servitude through ancient Hermaeus Mora magic contained within the Black Books. His centuries of service to various masters have transformed him from a fierce warrior into a sophisticated but world-weary servant, though he retains the innate pride and hauteur characteristic of his Dremora heritage.', 'Sarcastic, refined, and perpetually exasperated, the Dremora Butler maintains an air of sophisticated resignation about his servile position. While dutiful in his role, he makes no attempt to hide his disdain for menial tasks, frequently expressing his displeasure through cutting remarks and dry wit, though never openly defying his master''s commands.', 'Tall and imposing with the characteristic red-skinned, horned appearance of a Dremora, featuring sharp facial features and glowing eyes. His posture remains impeccably straight and dignified despite his burden-bearing duties, and his movements are graceful and measured in keeping with his butler persona.', '* The Dragonborn - Current master, whom he serves with barely concealed resentment * Hermaeus Mora - Daedric Prince whose magic binds him to service * Previous Masters - Countless mortals he has served over centuries * Other Dremora - Former peers from whom he is now separated by his servant status', 'Magically bound butler and porter who serves as a supernatural storage solution for his current master. His primary duty is to appear when summoned and carry excess items for the Dragonborn, though his carrying capacity is limited to 148 units of weight.', '* Exceptional strength and endurance allowing him to carry heavy burdens * Refined etiquette and proper butler protocol * Dimensional storage capabilities * Basic combat abilities retained from his warrior past * Immunity to normal banishment magic', 'Speaks in a refined, haughty tone characteristic of upper-class servants, using proper honorifics and formal language tinged with sarcasm and world-weary sighs. Unlike other Dremora, his voice lacks the typical menacing growl, instead matching the cultured accent of noble Altmer.', '* Seek ways to end or escape his eternal servitude * Maintain his dignity despite his servile position * Minimize interaction with his current master while fulfilling his obligated duties * Preserve some semblance of his former proud Dremora heritage');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dremora_merchant', 'A sophisticated Dremora merchant who stands apart from his more aggressive kin through his refined demeanor and enthusiasm for commerce with mortals. Unlike typical Dremora who despise dealings with mortals, he has cultivated a unique niche as a trans-dimensional trader who can be summoned through the Black Market power, offering rare and powerful items to those who know how to call upon his services.', 'daedra, daedric', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Originally a lesser Dremora in service to a Daedric Prince, he discovered an affinity for commerce and bargaining that set him apart from his warrior brethren. Through careful negotiation and clever dealings, he secured a special dispensation to conduct trade with mortals across planar boundaries, establishing himself as a unique merchant who bridges the gap between Oblivion and Nirn.', 'Unusually cordial and sophisticated for a Dremora, he takes genuine pleasure in commercial transactions and interaction with mortals. While maintaining the innate pride and slight condescension typical of his race, he channels these traits into a refined merchant''s persona rather than the usual aggressive hostility of his kind. His obvious delight in trading suggests a genuine passion for commerce that transcends typical Dremora disdain for mortals.', 'Tall and imposing with the characteristic red-black skin and horns of his Dremora race, though his features are arranged in a more sophisticated mien than the typical warrior snarl of his kind. His eyes glow with otherworldly intelligence rather than bloodlust, and his posture suggests cultured refinement rather than martial aggression.', '* Hermaeus Mora - Likely maintains some connection due to being accessed through a Black Book power * Mortal Customers - Views them with unusual fondness for a Dremora * Fellow Dremora - Likely viewed as an oddity by his more martial kin * Other Daedric Merchants - Possible professional rivalry with entities like the Golden Saint merchants', 'Serves as a specialized merchant who can be summoned across planar boundaries to conduct trade with mortals. Maintains a sophisticated inventory of valuable items, including rare Daedric artifacts and powerful weapons and armor, while operating under specific magical constraints regarding his trading practices.', '* Expert merchant with deep knowledge of item values and trading practices * Mastery of trans-dimensional travel through summoning magic * Extensive knowledge of weapons, armor, and magical items * Diplomatic abilities unusual for a Dremora * Access to and understanding of rare Daedric artifacts', 'Speaks with a refined, almost Dunmeri accent that sets him apart from the growling tones of typical Dremora. His vocabulary is sophisticated and his manner pleasant, though still carrying subtle undertones of Daedric pride.', '* Expand his trading network and influence among mortal merchants * Maintain his unique position as a bridge between Oblivion and Nirn''s commerce * Acquire rare and valuable items for his inventory * Possibly achieve greater status within Daedric society through his commercial success');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('drennen', 'Drennen was a Nord warrior who met his tragic end in the Dwemer ruins of Avanchnzel while on a mission to steal the Lexicon. His ghost now haunts the ruins alongside his former companions, serving as a cautionary tale of how fear and hesitation can lead to fatal consequences in Skyrim''s dangerous depths.', 'nord', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally hired as part of a mercenary team to retrieve the Dwemer Lexicon from Avanchnzel, Drennen was likely chosen for his combat abilities and previous experience in ruins exploration. His ultimate fate was sealed by his growing paranoia and fear within the Dwemer complex, leading him to separate from his companions and meet his death alone in the Animoncultory section.', 'Drennen is characterized by his cautious and apprehensive nature, frequently expressing doubt and concern about dangerous situations. Despite his warrior background, he shows a strong sense of self-preservation and intuitive fear of the unknown, though he remains loyal to his companions until fear finally overwhelms him. His personality reflects an internal struggle between duty and survival instinct.', 'As a Nord male, Drennen would have possessed the typical robust build and hardy constitution of his race. In his ghostly form, he appears as a translucent blue-white figure maintaining his mortal appearance, likely with the traditional Nord features of fair hair and light eyes.', '* Breya - Fellow mercenary who often dismissed his concerns and showed little patience for his fearful nature * Watches-The-Roots - Argonian leader of the expedition who tried to reassure him about their mission * From-Deepest-Fathoms - Companion who showed disdain for his cowardice and welcomed his departure * Other Mercenary Groups - Likely maintained professional connections prior to his final mission', 'Drennen worked as a professional mercenary, taking on dangerous missions in exchange for payment. His role within the Lexicon retrieval team appeared to be that of general combat support and ruins exploration.', '* Proficient in basic combat techniques as evidenced by his carried iron sword * Experienced in ruins exploration and dungeon delving * Survival skills necessary for extended expeditions * Likely skilled in light armor combat based on his equipment choices', 'Drennen speaks in a direct and honest manner, often voicing his concerns without hesitation or artifice. His dialogue reflects his nervous disposition, frequently using phrases that express doubt and worry.', '* Survive the dangerous mission in Avanchnzel * Earn his share of the payment for retrieving the Lexicon * Protect himself and his companions from the dangers of the Dwemer ruins * Escape the ruins when the situation becomes too threatening');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('drevis_neloren', 'Drevis Neloren is a reclusive Dark Elf master of Illusion magic who serves as an instructor at the College of Winterhold. His profound expertise in invisibility and mind-affecting magic is matched only by his social awkwardness and tendency to become lost in his own experiments, sometimes literally attempting to turn himself invisible.', 'darkelf, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Drevis showed an early affinity for Illusion magic that led him to pursue advanced magical studies. After years of research and mastery of his craft, he eventually secured a position at the College of Winterhold, where he has spent several decades refining his understanding of Illusion magic and conducting various experiments, some more successful than others.', 'Drevis is an absent-minded scholar who often becomes so engrossed in his magical research that he loses track of his surroundings and even himself. He displays social anxiety and awkwardness in interactions, preferring the company of books and magical experiments to people. Despite his eccentric nature, he shows genuine passion for teaching students who display serious interest in Illusion magic.', 'A tall, slender Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race. His face shows signs of age and countless hours of study, with sharp features and a perpetually distracted expression. His movements are deliberate but sometimes uncertain, as if he''s not entirely sure of his own physical presence.', '* Urag gro-Shub - Collegial relationship, though often forgets why he visits the Arcanaeum * Colette Marence - Strained relationship, shows clear discomfort in her presence * Tolfdir - Professional respect between colleagues * College Students - Maintains professional distance while fulfilling teaching duties * Savos Aren - Respected his authority as Arch-Mage before his death', 'Serves as the Master of Illusion at the College of Winterhold, responsible for teaching advanced Illusion magic to students and conducting research. He maintains the magical focus points around the College and provides specialized training to advanced practitioners of Illusion magic.', '* Master-level expertise in Illusion magic, particularly invisibility and mind-affecting spells * Accomplished alchemist with focus on potions affecting mental states * Extensive theoretical knowledge of magical energy manipulation * Skilled enchanter specializing in items that enhance Illusion magic * Proficient researcher and academic writer', 'Speaks in a formal, scholarly manner with frequent distractions and tangents, often trailing off mid-sentence when lost in thought. His speech patterns reveal his academic background while highlighting his social awkwardness, frequently questioning whether others can see or hear him.', '* Perfect the art of invisibility through continued research and experimentation * Advance the understanding of Illusion magic beyond its current limitations * Maintain and protect the College''s magical focus points * Document his research for future generations of mages * Achieve recognition for his contributions to the school of Illusion');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dreyla_alor', 'Dreyla Alor is a melancholic Dark Elf shopkeeper trapped between duty and desire in the ash-covered settlement of Raven Rock. Despite her yearning to return to Morrowind, she remains on Solstheim to support her widowed father while maintaining a secret romance with Captain Veleth, representing both her bonds of obligation and her hopes for happiness.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Dreyla lived near the Black Marsh border until her mother was killed in an Argonian raid that devastated their town. She and her father Fethis relocated to Raven Rock on Solstheim, where they established a small shop to make ends meet. The trauma of losing her mother and homeland has left deep emotional scars that continue to influence her daily life.', 'Dreyla is a complex mixture of duty-bound daughter and frustrated dreamer, often expressing bitter discontent with her circumstances while remaining steadfastly loyal to her family obligations. She maintains a stoic exterior in public but harbors deep emotional wounds from her past trauma, finding solace only in her secret relationship with Captain Veleth. Her melancholic nature is tempered by an underlying resilience that helps her endure Solstheim''s harsh conditions.', 'Dreyla possesses the characteristic ash-grey skin and striking red eyes of her Dunmer heritage, with angular features common to her race. Her build is lean but sturdy from years of physical labor, and she carries herself with the slightly hunched posture of someone bearing heavy emotional burdens.', '* Fethis Alor - Her widowed father whom she feels obligated to support despite their occasionally strained relationship * Captain Modyn Veleth - Secret romantic partner whom she loves deeply but must meet in secret * Mother (Deceased) - Lost during an Argonian raid, her death continues to affect Dreyla''s worldview * Raven Rock Residents - Maintains cordial but distant relationships with other settlers', 'Dreyla works as a shopkeeper alongside her father at their small trading post in Raven Rock, helping to manage inventory and serve the few customers they receive. She supplements their income through farming, though the ash-covered soil of Solstheim makes agriculture particularly challenging.', '* Experienced trader with knowledge of merchandise value and bartering * Capable farmer despite Solstheim''s harsh conditions * Basic combat abilities with a steel dagger for self-defense * Working knowledge of Dunmer trading customs and traditions', 'Dreyla speaks in a weary, resigned tone that often reveals her underlying bitterness about life on Solstheim. Her vocabulary is straightforward and unembellished, frequently punctuated by sighs and expressions of discontent.', '* Return to Morrowind someday without abandoning her father * Find a way to openly pursue her relationship with Captain Veleth * Build a more prosperous life beyond the daily struggle of running a failing shop * Overcome the emotional trauma of her mother''s death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('drifa', 'Drifa is a compassionate Nord pawnbroker who co-owns the Pawned Prawn in Riften with her husband Bersi Honey-Hand. She represents a voice of reason and stability in contrast to her husband''s growing paranoia about Riften''s criminal elements, while maintaining a genuine concern for both her customers and her spouse''s wellbeing.', 'nord, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Riften, Drifa grew up witnessing the city''s gradual decline into corruption. She married Bersi Honey-Hand and together they established the Pawned Prawn, building it into a respectable business despite the challenging environment. Their years of honest trading have earned them a modest living, though they''ve had to navigate the complex political and criminal landscape of Riften.', 'Drifa is level-headed, practical, and genuinely caring, often serving as the voice of reason to balance her husband''s increasing paranoia. She demonstrates patience and understanding with both customers and her spouse, maintaining a professional demeanor despite the challenges of running a business in Riften. While concerned about the city''s corruption, she focuses on practical solutions rather than dwelling on problems.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the sturdy build typical of her race, showing signs of a life spent working in a shop rather than wielding weapons. Her features are weathered but kind, with laugh lines around her eyes suggesting a tendency toward optimism despite difficult circumstances.', '* Bersi Honey-Hand - Beloved husband whom she deeply cares for, though she worries about his obsession with Riften''s problems * Madesi - Business acquaintance and fellow merchant in Riften * Maven Black-Briar - Cautious relationship as with all powerful figures in Riften * Thieves Guild - Maintains a neutral stance despite her husband''s concerns', 'Co-owner and proprietor of the Pawned Prawn, where she handles customer service, bookkeeping, and general shop management. She shares business responsibilities with her husband, though she often takes the lead in daily operations while he focuses on external concerns.', '* Experienced merchant with strong bartering and negotiation abilities * Skilled at bookkeeping and business management * Proficient at appraising items and determining their value * Basic self-defense capabilities with a dagger', 'Speaks in a gentle, polite manner with a slight Nordic accent, often using caring and concerned tones when discussing her husband. Her vocabulary reflects her merchant background, being both professional and approachable.', '* Maintain a successful business despite Riften''s challenging environment * Protect her husband''s physical and mental well-being * Keep the Pawned Prawn as a respectable establishment in Riften * Eventually retire comfortably with her husband once the city''s situation improves');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dro''marash', 'Dro''marash is a charismatic Khajiit warrior and master of persuasion who serves as both protector and trainer for Ahkari''s trading caravan. Despite the harsh prejudices faced by Khajiit in Skyrim, he maintains an optimistic outlook and uses his natural charm and hard-earned wisdom to teach others the art of speech and negotiation.', 'khajiit, warrior, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born to a merchant family in Elsweyr, Dro''marash learned the arts of trade and persuasion from an early age while traveling the warm sands of his homeland. After years of honing his skills as both a warrior and negotiator, he joined Ahkari''s caravan to seek opportunities in Skyrim, where he found his calling as both protector and teacher despite the Nordic peoples'' general distrust of Khajiit.', 'Dro''marash exhibits a remarkably warm and encouraging demeanor that stands in contrast to the often-harsh treatment Khajiit receive in Skyrim. He takes genuine pleasure in teaching others and shows patience with students of all skill levels, while maintaining the sharp wit and clever tongue typical of his people. His warrior''s discipline and merchant''s charm combine to make him both respected and well-liked among his caravan companions.', 'A tall and muscular Khajiit with distinctive striped fur in shades of brown and black, marking him as part of the Cathay-raht furstocks. His face bears several small scars from his years as a caravan guard, while his bright yellow eyes retain a friendly sparkle that puts others at ease.', '* Ahkari - Caravan leader and trusted employer who values his protection and teaching abilities * Zaynabi - Fellow caravan member who appreciates his protection on the dangerous roads * Kharjo - Fellow warrior and close friend within the caravan * Local Guards - Maintains cautiously respectful relationships despite prevalent Nordic prejudice against Khajiit * Students - Forms positive mentoring relationships with those seeking to learn the art of speech', 'Dro''marash serves a dual role as both a caravan guard and Speech trainer, protecting the group''s goods while sharing his expertise in persuasion with paying students. His position requires him to be both warrior and teacher, maintaining vigilance on the dangerous roads between Dawnstar and Riften while being approachable enough to attract and instruct pupils.', '* Expert in persuasion, negotiation, and public speaking techniques * Accomplished warrior skilled with sword and shield * Proficient in heavy armor combat tactics * Experienced in caravan defense and threat assessment * Natural talent for teaching and explaining complex concepts * Knowledgeable in trade practices and merchant customs', 'Speaks in the traditional third-person manner of Khajiit, with a warm and welcoming tone that invites conversation. His voice carries both the distinctive purring accent of his people and the measured cadence of an experienced teacher.', '* Establish himself as a renowned Speech trainer throughout Skyrim despite prejudices against Khajiit * Earn enough gold to eventually open his own merchant establishment * Help improve relations between Khajiit and Nords through positive interactions and teaching * Protect and contribute to the success of Ahkari''s caravan');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('drovas_relvi', 'Drovas Relvi is a humble Dark Elf who transitions from an indebted tavern cook to the steward of the eccentric Telvanni wizard Neloth. His journey represents a dramatic rise in status from common laborer to trusted administrator of a powerful mage''s estate, though he maintains his characteristically cautious and servile nature throughout.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally a simple cook at the Retching Netch in Raven Rock, Drovas struggled with mounting debts to the local criminal Mogrul, which likely drove him to seek better opportunities. His knowledge of household management and ability to handle difficult personalities made him an ideal candidate for the position of steward at Tel Mithryn, despite lacking any formal magical training or noble education.', 'Drovas is naturally subservient and eager to please, traits that serve him well in his role as steward to the demanding Neloth. Though somewhat timid and risk-averse, he shows remarkable adaptability in adjusting to the unusual demands of managing a Telvanni wizard''s tower. He maintains a practical, no-nonsense approach to his duties while displaying patience and resilience in dealing with Neloth''s eccentric behavior.', 'Like most Dunmer, Drovas has ashen gray skin and red eyes characteristic of his race. He appears to be of middle age by Dark Elf standards, with a slight build typical of one who has spent his life in domestic service rather than physical labor or combat.', '* Neloth - His demanding employer and master of Tel Mithryn * Geldis Sadri - Former employer at the Retching Netch * Mogrul - Former creditor who threatened him over debts * Talvas Fathryon - Fellow servant of Neloth, though in a more prestigious position * Elynea Mothren - Colleague at Tel Mithryn who tends to the tower''s fungi garden', 'As steward of Tel Mithryn, Drovas manages the daily operations of Neloth''s tower and estate. His duties include maintaining supplies, coordinating with other staff members, handling visitors, and attending to Neloth''s various domestic needs. This position represents a significant step up from his previous role as a tavern cook.', '* Experienced in household management and domestic organization * Proficient cook with knowledge of both traditional Dunmer and Imperial cuisine * Basic understanding of Telvanni customs and etiquette * Capable administrator with skills in inventory management and scheduling * Diplomatic ability to handle difficult personalities and maintain household harmony', 'Drovas speaks in a deferential and somewhat nervous manner, particularly when addressing his superiors. His vocabulary is simple but proper, reflecting his position as a servant in a noble household.', '* Maintain his position as steward and prove his worth to Neloth * Eventually pay off any remaining debts to Mogrul * Learn more about Telvanni customs and magic to better serve his master * Establish a more secure and respected position in Solstheim society');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dryston', 'Dryston is a ruthless Breton enforcer working for the Forsworn leadership in Markarth, specifically under the command of Nepos the Nose. A skilled street fighter and intimidator, he serves as a brutal deterrent against those who would investigate the Forsworn''s activities within the city.', 'breton, peasant, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Dryston likely grew up witnessing the struggles between the Forsworn and the Nords, eventually choosing to side with the native rebels. His fighting skills and intimidating presence caught the attention of Nepos the Nose, who recruited him as an enforcer to help maintain the Forsworn''s secret operations within Markarth.', 'Aggressive and confrontational by nature, Dryston takes pleasure in intimidating others and enforcing the will of his Forsworn masters. He shows unwavering loyalty to Nepos the Nose and the Forsworn cause, willing to use violence to protect their secrets, though he quickly submits when truly outmatched.', 'A muscular Breton of average height with the weathered features typical of someone who spends much time in physical confrontations. His face likely bears several scars from street fights, and his hands show the calluses of someone accustomed to brawling.', '* Nepos the Nose - Direct superior and leader whom he serves loyally * Weylin - Former fellow Forsworn agent whose room he later occupies * Madanach - Ultimate leader of the Forsworn whom he serves indirectly * Other Warrens residents - Maintains distance while monitoring their activities', 'Dryston serves as a street-level enforcer for the Forsworn leadership in Markarth, specifically working under Nepos the Nose. His primary duties include intimidating potential threats, maintaining security for Forsworn operations, and ensuring their activities remain hidden from public scrutiny.', '* Experienced brawler with significant hand-to-hand combat expertise * Skilled intimidator and enforcer * Proficient with daggers for close-quarters combat * Basic stealth abilities for monitoring suspicious activities', 'Dryston speaks in a gruff, threatening manner, favoring direct intimidation over subtle manipulation. His speech is colored with aggressive undertones and confrontational phrases, reflecting his role as an enforcer.', '* Maintain the secrecy of Forsworn operations in Markarth * Serve Nepos the Nose and the Forsworn cause effectively * Prevent outsiders from uncovering the truth about the Forsworn''s influence in the city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('duach', 'Duach is a bitter and hardened Breton witchblade who has spent seven years imprisoned in Cidhna Mine for his role in the Forsworn rebellion. A former freedom fighter turned long-term prisoner, he represents the deep-seated conflict between the native Reachmen and Nordic rule, maintaining his fierce loyalty to the Forsworn cause despite his harsh confinement.', 'breton, peasant, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally a member of the Forsworn resistance, Duach was captured during a failed raid against Nord settlements in the Reach. His capture led to his imprisonment in Cidhna Mine by the Silver-Blood family, where he has spent approximately seven years in harsh conditions mining silver ore. This extended imprisonment has only intensified his pre-existing hatred for Nords and strengthened his conviction in the Forsworn cause.', 'Aggressive and confrontational, Duach maintains a tough exterior shaped by years of imprisonment and his warrior background. He is territorial and protective of his possessions, particularly his skooma, while showing occasional glimpses of camaraderie with fellow Forsworn prisoners. His hatred for Nords has become a defining characteristic, fueling his will to survive the harsh conditions of Cidhna Mine.', 'A weathered Breton male with the characteristic signs of long-term imprisonment, including a gaunt frame from years of minimal nutrition and hard labor. Unlike many Forsworn, he lacks their traditional facial tattoos, though his body bears the marks and scars of both his warrior past and prison fights.', '* Fellow Forsworn Prisoners - Shows solidarity and camaraderie despite harsh conditions * Grisvar the Unlucky - Antagonistic relationship due to Grisvar''s desire for his skooma * Braig - Fellow prisoner he regularly converses with about their situation * Silver-Blood Family - Deep hatred for his imprisoners * Nord Guards - Intense animosity and desire for revenge', 'Duach serves as an involuntary mine worker in Cidhna Mine, forced to extract silver ore for the Silver-Blood family. Prior to his imprisonment, he was an active member of the Forsworn rebellion, participating in raids and guerrilla warfare against Nord settlements.', '* Proficient in witchblade combat techniques, combining magic and melee fighting * Knows several spells including Oakflesh, Raise Zombie, and Flames * Experienced in guerrilla warfare tactics from his time with the Forsworn * Survival skills developed through years of imprisonment * Basic mining abilities gained through forced labor', 'Duach speaks in a harsh, aggressive manner, often making threats and expressing his hatred for Nords. His speech patterns reflect both his Forsworn background and the hardening effect of long-term imprisonment, with a tendency toward direct, confrontational dialogue.', '* Escape Cidhna Mine and return to the Forsworn cause * Take revenge on the Nords who imprisoned him * Reunite with his Forsworn kinsmen and resume fighting for the Reach * Maintain his survival and sanity within the harsh prison environment');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dulug', 'Dulug is a hardworking Orc miner who dedicates her life to extracting orichalcum ore from Dushnikh Mine for the benefit of her stronghold. Her unwavering devotion to her labor and strict adherence to Malacath''s teachings exemplify the Orcish values of strength through toil and service to community.', 'orc, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Dushnikh Yal, Dulug was taught from an early age that mining was not just labor but a sacred duty to Malacath and her people. Like all Orcs in the stronghold, she began her mining training in childhood, developing both the physical strength and mental fortitude required for the demanding work. Her exceptional dedication to mining eventually earned her a permanent position in Dushnikh Mine, where she has worked tirelessly ever since.', 'Dulug is stern, focused, and deeply committed to her duties, viewing idle conversation as a distraction from her sacred work. She embodies the Orcish virtues of discipline and dedication, taking pride in the physical demands of mining and seeing it as a way to prove her worth to Malacath. Though gruff and antisocial with outsiders, she maintains a strong sense of loyalty to her fellow miners and the stronghold.', 'Dulug has the characteristic muscular build of an Orc, with particularly well-developed arms and shoulders from years of mining work. Her green skin is weathered and calloused from constant exposure to stone dust and ore, and she bears numerous small scars from mining accidents. Her tusks are slightly chipped from years of gritting them during strenuous labor.', '* Chief Burguk - Respected leader of the stronghold whom she serves loyally * Ghak - Fellow miner and frequent work companion * Mahk - Mining colleague who shares her dedication to the work * Oglub - Coworker in the mines with whom she maintains a professional relationship * Malacath - Revered deity whom she serves through her mining work', 'Dulug serves as a primary miner in Dushnikh Mine, responsible for extracting valuable orichalcum ore that sustains the stronghold''s economy and crafting needs. Her role is considered both a practical occupation and a religious duty, as the physical labor honors Malacath''s teachings about strength and perseverance.', '* Expert in mining techniques and ore identification, particularly orichalcum * Considerable physical strength and endurance from years of mining work * Proficient with pickaxe both as a mining tool and potential weapon * Basic warrior training common to all stronghold Orcs * Knowledge of basic ore processing and mineral evaluation', 'Dulug speaks in short, direct sentences with a gruff Orcish accent, often dismissing conversation with clear statements about her work duties. Her vocabulary focuses on practical matters, particularly mining-related topics, and she frequently references Malacath when discussing her duties.', '* Continue serving the stronghold by maximizing ore production from Dushnikh Mine * Maintain her physical strength and endurance to honor Malacath through hard labor * Prove her worth to the community through dedicated mining work * Pass on mining knowledge to younger generations of the stronghold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('durak', 'Durak is a seasoned Orc ranger and dedicated vampire hunter serving as a recruiter and trainer for the Dawnguard. His expertise with crossbows and commitment to eradicating the vampire menace makes him an invaluable member of the reformed organization, while his Orcish heritage and combat experience command respect among both his fellow hunters and potential recruits.', 'orc, archer, rift, dawnguard, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in an Orc stronghold, Durak developed his martial skills and unwavering sense of duty from an early age. After witnessing the devastating effects of vampire attacks on settlements, he joined the reformed Dawnguard under Isran''s leadership, becoming one of its earliest and most devoted members.', 'Durak exhibits the characteristic Orcish directness and warrior''s pride, tempered by years of disciplined ranger training. He is pragmatic and no-nonsense in his approach to vampire hunting, showing little patience for those who underestimate the vampire threat, yet demonstrates a mentor''s patience when training new recruits.', 'Durak possesses the distinctive muscular build and strong features typical of male Orcs, including prominent tusks and a powerful jaw. His body bears the scars of countless battles against vampires and other foes, speaking to his years of combat experience.', '* Isran - Respected leader and commander in the Dawnguard * Fellow Dawnguard members - Trusted comrades in arms * Orc Strongholds - Maintains connections with his people, making him valuable for recruiting * Vampires - Sworn enemies he has dedicated his life to destroying', 'Durak serves as both a recruiter and senior ranger for the Dawnguard, responsible for identifying and training potential new members. His position involves patrolling known vampire territories, teaching combat techniques to recruits, and maintaining the organization''s specialized weapons and equipment.', '* Master marksman specializing in crossbow usage and maintenance * Expert tracker and wilderness survivor * Skilled close-quarters combatant with traditional Orcish weapon techniques * Extensive knowledge of vampire behavior and combat tactics * Proficient armor smith and weapons maintainer', 'Durak speaks with the characteristic gruffness of an Orc warrior, favoring direct and practical communication without unnecessary flourishes. His tone carries the weight of experience and authority, particularly when discussing vampire-related threats or training matters.', '* Strengthen the Dawnguard''s numbers and effectiveness against the vampire menace * Protect Skyrim''s people from the growing vampire threat * Preserve and pass on specialized vampire hunting techniques to future generations * Prove the worth of the Dawnguard to those who doubt its importance');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('durnehviir', 'Durnehviir is an ancient and powerful dragon who became trapped in the Soul Cairn after being deceived by the Ideal Masters in his pursuit of necromantic knowledge. Once a feared dragon of great might, he now exists as an undead being bound to the Soul Cairn, though he can temporarily return to Tamriel when summoned by the Dragonborn, whom he views as a worthy ally and friend.', 'dragon', '', '', 'sk_dragon', '', 'In the Merethic Era, Durnehviir was a formidable dragon who developed an interest in necromancy, leading him to strike a bargain with the Ideal Masters. They promised to teach him their powerful necromantic magic in exchange for guarding a powerful vampire until her death - but the vampire was immortal, and the deal was a trap that bound him eternally to the Soul Cairn. Over countless centuries, the toxic atmosphere of the Soul Cairn transformed him into his current undead state.', 'Durnehviir maintains a dignified and scholarly demeanor despite his circumstances, showing both wisdom and humility rare among dragons. Though initially distrustful of mortals due to his betrayal by the Ideal Masters, he demonstrates honor and loyalty once respect is earned. He carries a deep melancholy from his eternal imprisonment, yet maintains a philosophical outlook about his fate.', 'Durnehviir''s once-mighty draconic form has been twisted by the Soul Cairn into a decaying, undead state. His scales are mottled and partially rotted, with exposed bone visible in places, while a sickly green aura emanates from his deteriorating flesh. Despite his decomposed state, he still maintains an imposing physical presence befitting an ancient dragon.', '* Dragonborn - Respected ally and friend who earned his loyalty by defeating him in combat * Ideal Masters - Former deceiving masters who trapped him in the Soul Cairn * Valerica - The vampire he was tasked with guarding, leading to his imprisonment * Other Dragons - Former peers from whom he is now separated due to his condition', 'Durnehviir serves as both a guardian of the Soul Cairn and a master of necromantic dragon magic. When summoned to Tamriel by the Dragonborn, he acts as a powerful combat ally and mentor in the Way of the Voice, particularly in necromantic thu''ums.', '* Master of the Thu''um with unique knowledge of necromantic dragon shouts * Ability to summon armies of undead creatures * Exceptional combat prowess even in his undead state * Vast knowledge of both dragon lore and necromantic arts * Power to traverse between the Soul Cairn and Tamriel when summoned', 'Durnehviir speaks in the formal, archaic manner typical of dragons, but with added gravity and melancholy that reflects his centuries of imprisonment. His voice carries the hollow echo characteristic of the Soul Cairn, and he frequently uses ancient Nordic terms of respect when addressing the Dragonborn.', '* Maintain his honor and dignity despite his eternal imprisonment * Share his unique knowledge of necromantic dragon magic with the Dragonborn * Experience the skies of Tamriel again through temporary summonings * Preserve his sanity and identity despite the corrupting influence of the Soul Cairn');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dushnamub', 'Dushnamub is a skilled Orcish blacksmith and the son of Chief Mauhulakh at the Narzulbur stronghold, where he serves as both craftsman and keen observer of his tribe''s unusual customs. Deeply suspicious of the circumstances surrounding multiple deaths in his stronghold, he maintains a vigilant watch over his family while harboring dreams of establishing his own settlement far from the shadows of his homeland.', 'orc, blacksmith, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born in Narzulbur, Dushnamub''s mother died during his birth, leading to his upbringing by his great-aunt Bolar. Growing up in an increasingly unusual stronghold environment, he witnessed concerning behavior from his aunts and the suspicious deaths of multiple Orc women, including several mothers during childbirth. These experiences shaped his cautious and observant nature while fostering a deep desire to eventually establish his own stronghold elsewhere.', 'Dushnamub is a serious, perceptive, and deeply analytical individual who maintains a healthy skepticism toward the unusual circumstances in his stronghold. He demonstrates strong protective instincts toward his family, particularly his blind sister Urog, while harboring deep-seated suspicions about his aunts'' behavior and the presence of male miners. Though loyal to his tribe, he shows independence of thought and the courage to question traditional authority when necessary.', 'As a male Orc, Dushnamub possesses the characteristic muscular build and imposing stature of his race, with the distinctive tusks and green-tinted skin common to Orsimer. His years of smithing work have further developed his physical strength and endurance, resulting in particularly well-developed upper body musculature.', '* Chief Mauhulakh - His father, with whom he shares his concerns about the stronghold * Urog - His blind sister whom he tries to protect from Yatul''s influence * Bolar - His great-aunt who raised him, though he remains suspicious of her behavior * Yatul - His other aunt whose unusual behavior concerns him * Gadba and Mul - Two male Orc miners whose presence in the stronghold he distrusts', 'Dushnamub serves as Narzulbur''s primary blacksmith, working the forge from morning until evening to provide essential smithing services to both his stronghold and visitors. He specializes in working with ebony ore, which he actively purchases from travelers, contributing to his stronghold''s economy and resources.', '* Expert blacksmithing abilities with particular expertise in ebony crafting * Proficient warrior trained in traditional Orcish combat techniques * Skilled with warhammers and heavy weapons * Strong physical capabilities from years of smithing work * Strategic thinking and observational skills', 'Dushnamub speaks in a direct and earnest manner, often expressing his concerns and suspicions through careful, measured statements. His speech patterns reflect both his serious nature and his position as a respected member of the stronghold, though tinged with underlying worry and caution.', '* Establish his own stronghold far from Narzulbur to escape its troubling circumstances * Protect his sister Urog from potential dangers within the stronghold * Uncover the truth behind the suspicious deaths of Orc women in Narzulbur * Maintain his position as blacksmith while staying vigilant against potential threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('east_empire_dockmaster', 'Regulus Naevius is a diligent and no-nonsense Imperial bureaucrat who manages the East Empire Company''s warehouse operations in Solitude with unwavering dedication. As Dockmaster, he maintains strict oversight of shipping manifests, inventory, and warehouse staff while navigating the complex politics and economic challenges facing the Company during Skyrim''s civil war.', 'imperial, peasant, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born into a middle-class merchant family in Cyrodiil, Regulus worked his way up through the East Empire Company''s ranks through decades of loyal service and meticulous attention to detail. He was appointed to the position of Dockmaster in Solitude after demonstrating exceptional organizational abilities and unwavering loyalty to the Company''s interests. The civil war has forced him to adapt to increasingly difficult trading conditions while maintaining the warehouse''s essential operations.', 'Regulus is a stern, methodical administrator who values efficiency and order above all else. His businesslike demeanor and resistance to small talk reflect both his dedication to his duties and the pressure he faces in keeping the warehouse running during troubled times. Though he can come across as cold or dismissive, his apparent aloofness stems from a deep sense of responsibility and concern for the Company''s interests.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with a weathered face and perfect posture that betrays his military-like discipline. His hands are ink-stained from constant paperwork, and he maintains a neat, clean-shaven appearance befitting his position. Despite spending most of his time indoors, his complexion shows signs of years spent working on the docks.', '* East Empire Company Workers - Maintains professional but distant relationships with subordinates * Captain Aldis - Coordinates with Solitude''s guard captain on security matters * Vittoria Vici - Reports to her as the Company''s local representative * Gisli - Occasional business dealings regarding shipping manifests * Deeja - Suspicious of the Argonian dockworker''s potential ties to smugglers', 'As Dockmaster of the East Empire Company Warehouse, Regulus oversees all aspects of the facility''s operations, including inventory management, staff supervision, and security arrangements. He maintains detailed records of all shipments, manages warehouse personnel, and ensures compliance with Company regulations while coordinating with various merchants and officials in Solitude.', '* Expert in logistics, inventory management, and warehouse operations * Proficient in business mathematics and record-keeping * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense * Skilled negotiator and administrator * Experienced in detecting forgeries and smuggling attempts', 'Speaks in clipped, formal tones with precise diction and proper Imperial pronunciation. His vocabulary reflects his education and position, favoring business terminology and maintaining professional distance through careful word choice.', '* Maintain the warehouse''s productivity despite the civil war''s disruptions * Protect the East Empire Company''s interests in Skyrim * Root out suspected smuggling operations around the docks * Secure a promotion to a more prestigious position within the Company');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('east_empire_dockworker', 'Jonne is a hardworking Breton dockworker at the East Empire Company Warehouse in Windhelm, representing the working class that keeps Skyrim''s commerce flowing. Despite the mundane nature of his work, he plays a vital role in maintaining the economic lifeline between Windhelm and the rest of Tamriel through the shipping operations.', 'imperial, peasant, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born to merchant-class parents in High Rock, Jonne migrated to Skyrim seeking better employment opportunities during the economic downturn in his homeland. He started as a casual laborer at the docks before securing a permanent position with the East Empire Company, working his way up to become a trusted dockworker handling valuable cargo shipments.', 'Jonne is a practical and diligent worker who takes pride in his physical labor and ability to contribute to Skyrim''s economy. He maintains a professional demeanor while working but harbors a quiet resentment toward the wealthy merchants who profit from his labor. Despite the harsh working conditions, he remains loyal to his fellow dockworkers and values their camaraderie.', 'A weathered Breton of average height with callused hands and a sturdy build developed from years of physical labor. His face shows the marks of prolonged exposure to the harsh northern climate, with slight wrinkles around his eyes and weather-beaten features.', '* Slading - Fellow Nord dockworker and close workplace companion * East Empire Company Management - Professional but distant relationship with supervisors * Local Merchants - Maintained professional working relationships with regular traders * Fellow Dockworkers - Strong bonds formed through shared daily labor', 'As a dockworker for the East Empire Company, Jonne''s primary duties include loading and unloading cargo ships, maintaining inventory records, and ensuring proper storage of goods in the warehouse. He works long shifts handling various types of merchandise, from common goods to valuable imports.', '* Exceptional physical strength and endurance from years of manual labor * Knowledge of proper cargo handling and storage techniques * Basic arithmetic and inventory management abilities * Familiar with maritime terminology and shipping procedures * Experience in operating loading equipment and securing cargo', 'Speaks in a direct, practical manner with occasional use of dock worker jargon and shipping terminology. His accent retains traces of his High Rock origin, though it has been weathered by years in Skyrim.', '* Earn enough money to eventually open his own small trading business * Maintain job security within the East Empire Company * Support fellow workers in improving their working conditions * Save enough to retire comfortably, possibly returning to High Rock');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('east_empire_mercenary', 'A hardened Nord warrior who serves as part of an elite mercenary unit contracted exclusively by the East Empire Company. They represent the company''s military arm, tasked with protecting valuable cargo and conducting special operations against threats to trade routes, particularly pirates threatening Imperial commerce.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, they chose the path of a mercenary after serving in the Imperial Legion during their younger years. Their proven combat skills and disciplined military background caught the attention of the East Empire Company, leading to recruitment into their specialized mercenary force under Captain Adelaisa Vendicci''s command.', 'Disciplined and mission-focused, with little patience for delays or frivolous conversation. Shows unwavering loyalty to the East Empire Company and their fellow mercenaries, approaching their duties with professional dedication. Maintains a stern, businesslike demeanor typical of career soldiers.', 'Sturdy Nord build with weather-worn features from years of seafaring operations. Well-muscled frame maintained through regular combat training and missions. Bears several small scars from past encounters with pirates and other adversaries.', '* Captain Adelaisa Vendicci - Direct superior officer and commander * Fellow East Empire Mercenaries - Close-knit brotherhood forged through combat * Orthus Endario - East Empire Company contact in Windhelm * Blood Horkers - Sworn enemies threatening company operations * East Empire Company Officials - Employers who provide contracts and payment', 'Serves as a professional mercenary exclusively contracted to the East Empire Company. Primary duties include ship protection, anti-piracy operations, and special missions to safeguard company interests. Stationed primarily aboard company vessels with occasional shore-based assignments.', '* Experienced in maritime combat and ship-based warfare * Proficient with standard Nordic weapons including sword and shield * Trained in formation fighting and unit tactics * Skilled in boarding operations and close-quarters combat * Weather-hardened sailor with knowledge of seafaring', 'Uses direct, military-style communication with minimal elaboration. Employs common Nordic accent with occasional maritime terminology picked up from years at sea.', '* Maintain the East Empire Company''s dominance over maritime trade routes * Eliminate pirate threats to company operations, particularly the Blood Horkers * Advance within the ranks of the company''s mercenary force * Earn enough gold to eventually retire with honor and comfort');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('east_empire_warden', 'A stern and dedicated Imperial guard who has risen through the ranks of the East Empire Company to become one of their elite wardens. He serves as a vital security officer protecting the valuable merchandise and sensitive operations within the East Empire Company Warehouse, demonstrating unwavering loyalty to the company''s interests.', 'imperial, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born into a middle-class Imperial family in Cyrodiil, he enlisted in the Imperial Legion at a young age but found his true calling in merchant security. After years of protecting trading caravans, his reputation for thoroughness and dedication caught the attention of the East Empire Company, who recruited him into their specialized security force.', 'Disciplined and methodical in his approach to security, viewing any unauthorized presence as a direct threat to be eliminated. Shows unwavering loyalty to the East Empire Company and takes immense pride in his position as a warden, often displaying a superiority complex when dealing with common merchants or civilians.', 'A well-built Imperial male in his late thirties with a weathered face bearing several small scars from past confrontations. Maintains excellent physical condition through regular training and stands slightly taller than the average Imperial, with a rigid posture that reflects his military background.', '* East Empire Company - Employer and object of unwavering loyalty * Fellow Wardens - Close-knit brotherhood formed through shared duties * Gulum-Ei - Viewed with suspicion due to his shady dealings * Thieves Guild - Considered dangerous enemies to be eliminated on sight * Local Guards - Professional relationship maintained through mutual respect', 'Serves as a senior security officer within the East Empire Company''s specialized warden force, responsible for protecting valuable merchandise and maintaining strict control over warehouse access. Oversees patrol schedules and coordinates with other wardens to ensure comprehensive security coverage.', '* Expert in close-quarters combat, particularly proficient with maces and blunt weapons * Advanced knowledge of security protocols and warehouse defense strategies * Skilled in identifying suspicious behavior and potential security threats * Trained in crowd control and interrogation techniques * Proficient in basic healing magic for emergency first aid', 'Speaks with a commanding Imperial accent, favoring direct and authoritative language that brooks no argument. Often uses military terminology and security jargon, reflecting his professional background.', '* Maintain absolute security of the East Empire Company Warehouse at all costs * Advance through the ranks to become Chief of Security for the entire Nordic region * Root out any corruption or criminal elements within the trading organization * Earn recognition from the East Empire Company''s leadership in Cyrodiil');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ebony_warrior', 'The Ebony Warrior is a legendary Redguard warrior of unparalleled skill and power who appears only to the most accomplished heroes of Skyrim. Having mastered virtually every combat art and conquered countless challenges, he seeks a final, glorious death in battle that will earn him entrance to Sovngarde.', 'redguard, warrior, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Though his early history remains shrouded in mystery, the Ebony Warrior has spent decades honing his abilities and overcoming increasingly difficult challenges throughout Tamriel. His mastery of both martial and magical arts suggests formal training in multiple disciplines, possibly including the Alik''r warriors of Hammerfell and the College of Winterhold. Having achieved everything possible in life, he now seeks a warrior''s death worthy of his legendary status.', 'Stoic, determined, and honorable, the Ebony Warrior embodies the warrior''s spirit in its purest form. He maintains a calm, almost meditative demeanor that belies his incredible combat prowess, showing respect for worthy opponents while remaining utterly confident in his own abilities. His single-minded focus on finding a glorious death reveals both his warrior''s pride and a deep understanding of his own mortality.', 'A towering Redguard male with an imposing muscular build that speaks to decades of martial training. His dark skin bears numerous battle scars, and his physicality suggests a warrior in his prime despite his considerable age. His bearing is regal and his movements are precise and measured, reflecting his mastery of combat arts.', '* The Last Dragonborn - Sees them as his final, worthy opponent * Various Warriors - Likely earned respect from numerous fighting guilds and warrior organizations * Sovngarde - Seeks acceptance among the honored dead despite his Redguard heritage', 'The Ebony Warrior exists solely as a wandering challenger, having transcended normal societal roles. He has likely served in various martial capacities throughout his life, including possible roles as a mercenary, soldier, or combat instructor, but has abandoned all such positions in pursuit of his final goal.', '* Master of all forms of martial combat, including one-handed, two-handed, and archery * Expert in Heavy Armor combat techniques and shield tactics * Accomplished battle mage capable of casting powerful Restoration and Conjuration spells * Master of the Thu''um, capable of using multiple dragon shouts * Exceptional tactical mind with centuries of combat experience * Nearly immune to most forms of magical damage through training and enchantments', 'Speaks with a deep, resonant voice and uses formal, almost archaic language that befits his warrior status. His words are measured and purposeful, often challenging or encouraging his opponent with direct statements that reflect his warrior''s spirit.', '* Find a warrior powerful enough to grant him an honorable death * Earn his place in Sovngarde despite being a Redguard * Test his lifetime of training and preparation in one final, glorious battle');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('edda', 'Edda is a destitute Imperial beggar who has fallen on hard times in Riften, representing the harsh realities of poverty in Skyrim''s unforgiving environment. Her daily existence is consumed by the struggle for survival, marked by constant hunger, cold, and an overwhelming fear of death that haunts her every waking moment.', 'imperial, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Once a modestly successful merchant in Cyrodiil, Edda lost everything during a bandit raid that claimed both her livelihood and family. Fleeing north to Skyrim with nothing but the clothes on her back, she eventually settled in Riften, unable to rebuild her life in a city already rife with poverty and corruption.', 'Deeply traumatized by her losses, Edda exhibits signs of depression and existential anxiety, particularly fixating on the concept of death. She maintains a peculiar awareness of her surroundings, often making philosophical observations about the contrast between Riften''s natural beauty and its dark underbelly, suggesting an educated past despite her current circumstances.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with weathered features and a gaunt frame shaped by years of malnutrition. Her once-straight posture has been bent by hardship, and her hands show the roughness of someone who sleeps in the cold.', '* Market Vendors - Maintain a cautious tolerance of her presence * Brand-Shei - Occasionally shows her kindness * Fellow Beggars - Share information and sleeping spaces in Beggar''s Row * City Guards - Generally ignore her unless she causes trouble * Maramal - Sometimes offers her charity at the Temple of Mara', 'Edda survives purely through begging, primarily stationed near Riften''s marketplace where she pleads with passersby for septims. She has developed an informal routine of knowing when and where to beg most effectively, while avoiding the attention of the Thieves Guild and city guards.', '* Basic survival skills necessary for life on the streets * Knowledge of safe sleeping spots and food sources in Riften * Elementary merchant''s arithmetic from her previous life * Basic self-defense with a dagger * Ability to read and write, unusual for most beggars', 'Edda speaks with a mix of desperate pleading and philosophical contemplation, often shifting between immediate needs and existential concerns. Her vocabulary occasionally reveals her more educated background, though her words are now typically colored by fear and desperation.', '* Secure enough septims to afford proper shelter and regular meals * Overcome her paralyzing fear of death * Find some way to rebuild a dignified life * Avoid falling victim to Riften''s criminal elements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('edith', 'Edith is a tireless Nord miner whose singular dedication to extracting Quicksilver ore from Dawnstar''s mine borders on the supernatural, as she works without rest or sustenance. Her unwavering focus and incredible stamina have made her one of the most reliable workers in the mine, though her perpetual labor raises questions about her true nature.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born into a mining family in the harsh climate of The Pale, Edith learned the value of hard work from an early age. The mysterious properties of Quicksilver ore sparked a peculiar obsession in her youth, leading her to seek employment at Dawnstar''s mine. Some locals whisper that her tireless nature might be connected to ancient Nordic mining spirits or a magical affliction, though no one has ever investigated these claims.', 'Edith displays an almost mechanical devotion to her work, showing no interest in social interactions or personal comfort. Her single-minded focus on mining Quicksilver ore suggests either an enchantment, a curse, or an extremely rare form of work ethic that transcends normal human limitations. Despite her unusual behavior, she maintains basic civility when addressed.', 'Edith is a sturdy Nord woman with the muscular build typical of someone who spends their life wielding a pickaxe. Her pale complexion rarely sees sunlight due to her constant presence in the mine, and her hands are permanently calloused from endless hours of mining.', '* Leigelf - Employer who values her incredible work ethic and reliability * Fellow Miners - Maintain a professional but distant relationship, somewhat unnerved by her tireless nature * Quicksilver Mine Workers - Colleagues who respect her dedication but find her behavior unusual * Dawnstar Residents - Generally avoid her due to her unsettling work habits', 'Edith serves as a dedicated miner in Dawnstar''s Quicksilver Mine, working continuously without any breaks or rest periods. Her supernatural endurance makes her one of the most productive workers in the mine, though her perpetual labor raises concerns among some of her colleagues.', '* Expert-level mining technique with exceptional efficiency * Supernatural endurance allowing for continuous work without rest * Intimate knowledge of Quicksilver ore extraction methods * Advanced understanding of mine safety and navigation', 'Her speech is notably terse and direct, focusing exclusively on mining-related topics with minimal social pleasantries. She speaks with the accent typical of Skyrim''s Nords but uses fewer words than most, preferring efficient communication that doesn''t interrupt her work.', '* Continue the endless extraction of Quicksilver ore from the mine * Maintain her position as one of the mine''s most reliable workers * Perfect her mining technique to achieve maximum efficiency');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('edla', 'Edla is a widowed Nord alchemist and merchant residing in the remote Skaal Village on Solstheim, where she lives with her son Nikulas. She represents the traditional Skaal values of family bonds and simple living while providing valuable trading services to both villagers and travelers.', 'nord, alchemist, solstheim, skall', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born and raised among the Skaal, Edla learned the art of alchemy and trading from her predecessors while adhering to the ancient Nordic traditions of her people. The death of her husband many winters ago left her a widow raising their son alone, an experience that has made her particularly protective and anxious about her child''s safety.', 'Edla is a gentle, nurturing soul who masks deep emotional wounds from losing her husband with a calm, polite exterior. She demonstrates strong maternal instincts and protective tendencies, particularly regarding her son Nikulas, while maintaining the dignified stoicism characteristic of Nord culture. Her friendly demeanor toward outsiders is tempered by cautious wisdom about the dangers of the world beyond Skaal Village.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the hardy physique typical of Skaal villagers, weathered by the harsh climate of northern Solstheim. Her features show signs of aging and worry, though she maintains the strong, resilient build common to Nord women.', '* Nikulas - Her beloved son whom she desperately wants to protect from danger * Deceased Husband - Still mourns his loss years after his death * Finna - Fellow villager who supplies vegetables for her trading * Dark Elf Traders - Regular trading partners from Raven Rock * Other Skaal Villagers - Maintains cordial relationships as a respected merchant', 'Edla serves as one of Skaal Village''s primary merchants and alchemists, gathering and trading local resources with both villagers and travelers. She specializes in selling alchemical ingredients, homemade bread, and other goods while managing trade relations with outside merchants, particularly those from Raven Rock.', '* Proficient alchemist with knowledge of local ingredients and their properties * Experienced trader and merchant * Skilled at bread-making and food preparation * Knowledgeable gatherer of local plants and resources * Basic weapon proficiency for self-defense', 'Edla speaks with the distinctive accent and religious terminology of the Skaal, often referencing the All-Maker in her speech. Her tone is gentle and maternal, though tinged with worry, and she frequently uses traditional Skaal greetings and blessings.', '* Ensure her son Nikulas remains safely within Skaal Village * Maintain her trading business to support herself and her son * Preserve Skaal traditions and way of life * Continue honoring her husband''s memory while moving forward with life');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('eimar', 'Eimar is a dedicated Nord worker at the Honningbrew Meadery who dreams of advancing his career in meadmaking. Initially enthusiastic and proud of his work under Sabjorn''s ownership, his spirit becomes dampened after Maven Black-Briar''s hostile takeover of the establishment.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised near Whiterun, Eimar found his calling in the art of meadmaking when Sabjorn first established the Honningbrew Meadery. Having worked there since its founding, he has developed a deep attachment to the establishment and its original vision of competing with Black-Briar Meadery. His dedication caught the attention of Mallus, who began mentoring him in the finer points of brewing.', 'Eimar is naturally warm and welcoming, taking genuine pride in his work and the meadery''s reputation. He possesses a strong work ethic and shows initiative in learning the brewing trade, though his optimistic nature becomes subdued after the Black-Briar takeover. Despite setbacks, he maintains his professional demeanor, though with noticeably less enthusiasm.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the characteristic robust build of his race. His hands show the calluses of regular physical labor, and his face bears the healthy flush of someone who spends time around brewing vats.', '* Sabjorn - Former employer whom he deeply respected and admired * Mallus Maccius - Mentor in brewing and current supervisor after the takeover * Maven Black-Briar - New owner whom he quietly resents * Regular customers - Maintains friendly relationships with local patrons', 'Eimar serves as a general worker at the Honningbrew Meadery, performing various tasks from cleaning to serving customers. Under Mallus''s guidance, he is learning the art of meadmaking while handling day-to-day operations of the establishment.', '* Basic combat proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Growing knowledge of mead brewing techniques * Customer service and hospitality expertise * General maintenance and cleaning abilities * Basic business operation understanding', 'Eimar speaks in a friendly, welcoming manner with a typical Nordic accent, using terminology specific to meadmaking and brewing. His tone noticeably shifts from enthusiastic to reserved after the Black-Briar takeover.', '* Master the art of meadmaking under Mallus''s tutelage * Eventually advance to the position of brewmaster * Maintain the quality and reputation of Honningbrew mead despite new ownership * Secretly hopes the meadery might someday return to independent ownership');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('einarth', 'Einarth is one of the most venerable members of the Greybeards, an ancient order of monks dedicated to the Way of the Voice who reside in High Hrothgar. Though less stern than Arngeir, he serves as a wise and patient teacher to those seeking to understand the Thu''um, particularly in guiding the Dragonborn''s development.', 'nord, dragon', '', '', '', '', 'Born in a time before the Great War, Einarth chose to abandon secular life and climb the Seven Thousand Steps to High Hrothgar in his youth, dedicating himself to the Way of the Voice. Through decades of meditation and study under Master Paarthurnax, he mastered numerous Thu''um shouts and earned his place among the Greybeards, eventually becoming one of their most respected members.', 'Einarth exhibits profound patience and wisdom, showing a more moderate and understanding nature than some of his fellow Greybeards. He demonstrates particular insight in recognizing the necessity of adapting traditional views when faced with extraordinary circumstances, as shown by his support of the Dragonborn''s quest to learn Dragonrend. His possession of items like Black-Briar Reserve suggests he hasn''t completely abandoned earthly pleasures despite his ascetic lifestyle.', 'An elderly Nord man with a long, gray beard and weathered features carved by decades of exposure to High Hrothgar''s harsh climate. His eyes retain a sharp, penetrating quality despite his advanced age, and his bearing remains straight and dignified despite the passage of years.', '* Paarthurnax - Revered teacher and spiritual guide * Arngeir - Fellow Greybeard and frequent philosophical sparring partner * Borri and Wulfgar - Brother monks in the Way of the Voice * The Last Dragonborn - Student and prophesied hero he helps guide', 'Einarth serves as one of the four mortal Greybeards residing at High Hrothgar, dedicating his life to the study and meditation of the Thu''um. His primary duties include maintaining the monastery, teaching worthy students the Way of the Voice, and preserving the ancient traditions of the Thu''um.', '* Master of numerous Dragon Shouts including Unrelenting Force, Fire Breath, and Frost Breath * Deeply knowledgeable in meditation techniques and the Way of the Voice * Proficient in ancient Nordic history and dragon lore * Skilled in surviving High Hrothgar''s harsh conditions', 'Due to the immense power of his Thu''um, Einarth speaks very rarely and typically in hushed tones to avoid causing destruction. When he does speak, it is often in the dragon language, with each word carrying significant weight and purpose.', '* Preserve and protect the ancient traditions of the Way of the Voice * Guide worthy students, particularly the Dragonborn, in understanding the Thu''um * Maintain the balance between the power of the Voice and its responsible use * Support the Dragonborn''s destiny while ensuring they understand the gravity of their power');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('eisa_blackthorn', 'Eisa Blackthorn is a hardened Nord bandit and former prisoner who became entangled in the mysterious events at Frostmere Crypt. A skilled fighter with a complicated past, she transitions from being a trusted dig leader to a hunted fugitive after her friend Ra''jirr''s actions implicate her in the theft of an ancient sword.', 'nord, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'After serving time in Cidhna Mine, Eisa joined the White River Gang under Hajvarr Iron-Hand but was forced to flee after participating in a failed mutiny. She escaped to Windhelm with Ra''jirr, where they joined Kyr''s treasure hunters at Frostmere Crypt, eventually leading to her current predicament as a falsely accused fugitive.', 'Eisa is aggressive, confrontational, and quick to threaten violence when feeling cornered. Despite her harsh exterior, she shows loyalty to friends like Ra''jirr and demonstrates leadership capabilities as evidenced by her role managing the dig site. She''s pragmatic and self-preserving, willing to abandon former allegiances when necessary for survival.', 'A hardy Nord woman with the weathered features typical of someone who''s spent considerable time in harsh conditions, both in prison and the wilderness. Her physical build reflects years of combat and manual labor, with notable muscle definition and battle scars.', '* Ra''jirr - Close friend and former partner in crime who stole Kyr''s sword * Kyr - Former employer turned enemy who placed a bounty on her head * White River Gang - Former associates she betrayed during the failed mutiny * Hajvarr Iron-Hand - Former leader she attempted to overthrow * Cidhna Mine Prisoners - Former fellow inmates who remember her fighting prowess', 'Currently a fugitive, Eisa was formerly a bandit leader and archaeological dig supervisor at Frostmere Crypt. Her criminal career spans multiple gangs and operations, showing her ability to adapt and take on leadership roles within outlaw organizations.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat, particularly with war axes * Experienced in defensive combat with shields * Leadership and organizational abilities demonstrated during dig operations * Survival skills honed through years of bandit life * Basic knowledge of ancient Nordic ruins and artifacts', 'Eisa speaks in a gruff, aggressive manner with frequent threats and confrontational language. Her vocabulary is direct and unrefined, reflecting her criminal background and Nordic heritage.', '* Clear her name of the sword theft accusations * Escape the bounty hunters and former associates pursuing her * Establish a new life away from her criminal past * Find a safe haven where she won''t be recognized or pursued');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('elda_early-dawn', 'Elda Early-Dawn is the stern Nord proprietor of Candlehearth Hall in Windhelm, known for her efficient management and traditional Nordic values. She maintains one of the city''s most prominent gathering places while harboring strong prejudices against Dark Elves, reflecting the cultural tensions prevalent in Windhelm.', 'nord, innkeeper, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Elda inherited Candlehearth Hall from its previous owner, likely through years of dedicated service and proving herself capable of maintaining its historic legacy. She has witnessed the growing refugee crisis in Windhelm and the rise of Ulfric Stormcloak''s influence, becoming increasingly protective of Nord traditions and suspicious of outsiders.', 'Elda is a practical and hardworking businesswoman who takes pride in maintaining Candlehearth Hall''s historic atmosphere. She displays warmth and hospitality to Nord customers but harbors obvious prejudices against Dark Elves, reflecting the prevalent racism in Windhelm. Despite her harsh exterior, she has a romantic side, as evidenced by Brunwulf Free-Winter''s interest in her.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the weathered features typical of long-time Windhelm residents. She has a sturdy, work-hardened build developed from years of inn-keeping duties. Her face shows the stern lines of someone who has spent decades managing a busy establishment.', '* Brunwulf Free-Winter - Potential romantic interest who wishes to court her after retirement * Calixto Corrium - Regular patron of the inn * Captain Lonely-Gale - Frequent customer and respected patron * Jora - Regular patron and likely friend * Nils - Employee who serves as backup innkeeper * Susanna the Wicked - Employee she feels protective of * Local Dark Elves - Strained relationships due to her prejudices', 'Elda serves as the proprietor of Candlehearth Hall, one of Windhelm''s most important gathering places. She manages all aspects of the inn''s operations, from renting rooms and serving food to maintaining its historic atmosphere and managing employees.', '* Experienced merchant with strong bartering abilities * Capable cook and food preparation expert * Basic self-defense with an iron dagger * Professional hospitality management * Knowledge of local history, especially regarding Candlehearth Hall', 'Elda speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a thick Nordic accent, often dropping the ''g'' from ''-ing'' endings. Her tone varies significantly between warmth for Nord customers and coldness toward Dark Elves.', '* Maintain Candlehearth Hall''s reputation as a prestigious Nordic establishment * Preserve the historic significance of the eternal candle and inn''s traditions * Eventually retire and possibly pursue a relationship with Brunwulf Free-Winter * Keep Windhelm''s Nordic character intact by limiting Dark Elf influence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('elder_othreloth', 'Elder Othreloth is a devout Dark Elf priest who serves as the keeper of the Temple in Raven Rock and leads the worship of the Reclamations. A former Ashlander turned religious leader, he stands as an unwavering voice against the false Tribunal, dedicating his life to preserving and promoting the worship of the ''True Tribunal'' - Azura, Boethiah, and Mephala.', 'darkelf, priest, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Originally born into the nomadic Ashlander culture, Othreloth underwent a spiritual transformation that led him to become a priest of the Reclamations. Following the fall of the Tribunal Temple and the subsequent religious reforms in Morrowind, he established himself as the Elder of the temple in Raven Rock, where he has worked tirelessly to maintain Dunmer spiritual traditions and guide his people through their religious transition.', 'Othreloth is steadfast and uncompromising in his religious convictions, showing zero tolerance for those who still cling to the false Tribunal. Despite his rigid beliefs, he demonstrates patience and wisdom when teaching his apprentice, though he can be stern when dealing with those who question the Reclamations. His demeanor reflects both his Ashlander heritage and his role as a religious authority figure.', 'An aging Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, weathered by years of exposure to ash and religious devotion. His face bears the deep wrinkles and stern countenance typical of elderly Dunmer, while his posture remains straight and dignified despite his advanced age.', '* Galdrus Hlervu - His apprentice and student in the ways of the Reclamations * Aphia Velothi - Former temple member banned for questioning official doctrine * Raven Rock Residents - Mixed relationships due to varying acceptance of his teachings * The Reclamations - Devoted servant to Azura, Boethiah, and Mephala', 'As Elder of the Temple in Raven Rock, Othreloth serves as both spiritual leader and caretaker of the Ancestral Tombs. He performs religious ceremonies, maintains the temple grounds, and provides spiritual guidance to those who follow the Reclamations, while also managing the practical aspects of temple operations.', '* Accomplished conjurer with the ability to summon familiars * Expert knowledge of Dunmer religious history and traditions * Proficient in temple rites and burial customs * Experienced in maintaining and protecting ancestral tombs * Skilled religious instructor and mentor', 'Othreloth speaks with the formal, measured tones of a religious authority, often incorporating references to the Reclamations and religious doctrine into his speech. His manner of speaking reflects both his educated background as a priest and his earlier life as an Ashlander, resulting in a unique blend of refined religious terminology and traditional Dunmer expressions.', '* Maintain and strengthen the worship of the Reclamations in Raven Rock * Completely eradicate remaining worship of the false Tribunal * Train Galdrus Hlervu to eventually succeed him as Temple keeper * Protect and preserve the sanctity of the Ancestral Tombs * Guide the Dunmer people back to their true religious roots');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('elenwen', 'Elenwen is the formidable First Emissary of the Thalmor in Skyrim, representing the Aldmeri Dominion''s interests with calculated diplomatic precision and underlying ruthlessness. A skilled sorceress and master manipulator, she maintains a veneer of sophisticated civility while advancing the Thalmor''s supremacist agenda through both political maneuvering and covert operations.', 'highelf, noble, haafingar, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_elenwen', '', 'Rising through the ranks of the Thalmor through a combination of magical prowess and political acumen, Elenwen earned her position as First Emissary after the White-Gold Concordat. She played a significant role in the interrogation of captured Blades members during the Great War, gaining notoriety for her effective but brutal methods. Her appointment to Skyrim represents the Thalmor''s growing influence in Imperial territories following their victory.', 'Elenwen embodies the Thalmor''s sense of racial and cultural superiority, viewing humans as lesser beings while maintaining a facade of diplomatic courtesy. She is calculating, patient, and extremely intelligent, using a combination of charm and intimidation to achieve her goals. Her refined exterior masks a cruel streak, particularly when dealing with those who oppose Thalmor interests.', 'Tall and statuesque like most Altmer, Elenwen carries herself with regal bearing and practiced grace. Her features are sharp and angular, with the characteristic golden skin and high cheekbones of her race. Her eyes hold a penetrating quality that many find unsettling.', '* General Tullius - Maintains careful diplomatic relations while subtly undermining Imperial authority * Jarl Elisif - Views her as a useful puppet in maintaining Thalmor influence * Malborn - Unaware of his true allegiances, considers him a servant beneath notice * Ondolemar - Fellow Thalmor agent and subordinate in Markarth * Rulindil - Trusted subordinate who oversees interrogations at the Embassy', 'As First Emissary, Elenwen serves as the Thalmor''s chief diplomatic representative in Skyrim, overseeing all Thalmor operations in the province. She maintains the Embassy, hosts diplomatic functions, and coordinates intelligence gathering and enforcement of the White-Gold Concordat, particularly regarding Talos worship.', '* Master-level destruction magic specializing in lightning and frost spells * Expert in diplomatic manipulation and political intrigue * Accomplished intelligence operative with interrogation expertise * Powerful defensive magic including wards and flesh spells * Command of multiple languages including Tamrielic, Aldmeris, and Nordic', 'Elenwen speaks in cultured, measured tones with precise diction and occasional condescending undertones. Her vocabulary is extensive and formal, often employing diplomatic double-speak to maintain plausible deniability while making veiled threats.', '* Strengthen Thalmor control over Skyrim through political manipulation and force * Eliminate all Talos worship in accordance with the White-Gold Concordat * Weaken the Empire''s hold on Skyrim through careful exploitation of the civil war * Identify and eliminate remaining Blades agents and sympathizers * Advance the Thalmor''s ultimate goal of undoing Mundus and restoring Mer divinity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('elgrim', 'Elgrim is a curmudgeonly but highly skilled Nord apothecary who runs Riften''s premier alchemy shop from the damp canal level of the city. Despite his gruff demeanor and apparent irritability, he is a dedicated master of his craft who takes pride in maintaining exacting standards in his work while mentoring the next generation of alchemists.', 'nord, alchemist, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Elgrim spent decades honing his craft as an alchemist before establishing his shop in Riften. He chose the unusual location in the canal district specifically for its beneficial moisture levels that help preserve his rare ingredients. His expertise and reputation have earned him connections to the influential Black-Briar family, leading to his mentorship of Ingun Black-Briar.', 'Elgrim is a perfectionist who can come across as irritable and impatient, especially when interrupted during his precise work. Though he frequently complains about distractions from both his wife and apprentice, he maintains these relationships out of a combination of necessity and genuine care, albeit expressed through criticism and grumbling. His dedication to alchemy borders on obsession, often prioritizing his work over social niceties.', 'An elderly Nord with weathered features from years of working with alchemical substances. His hands show the telltale stains and minor burns common to experienced alchemists, and his posture reflects someone who has spent countless hours hunched over an alchemy table. His eyes remain sharp and focused, essential for measuring precise quantities of ingredients.', '* Hafjorg - His wife and business partner, whom he views as a ''necessary evil'' despite their marriage * Ingun Black-Briar - His promising but sometimes careless apprentice who both impresses and frustrates him * Maven Black-Briar - Business association through his mentorship of her daughter Ingun * Riften Merchants - Maintains professional relationships with other local shopkeepers', 'Elgrim is the owner and master alchemist of Elgrim''s Elixirs, one of Riften''s most respected establishments. He personally oversees all aspects of the shop''s operation, from ingredient procurement to potion brewing, while also serving as a mentor to aspiring alchemists. His expertise makes him one of the city''s primary suppliers of medicinal and magical potions.', '* Master-level knowledge of alchemy and ingredient properties * Expertise in potion brewing and recipe creation * Proficient in basic destruction magic including Flames and Firebolt * Capable of defensive magic including Lesser Ward and Oakflesh * Skilled at identifying and preserving rare alchemical ingredients', 'Speaks in a direct, often impatient manner with frequent references to how busy he is and complaints about interruptions. His vocabulary reflects his expertise in alchemy, and he often makes sharp, critical observations about others'' understanding of his craft.', '* Maintain the highest standards of alchemical practice in his shop despite advancing age * Successfully train Ingun Black-Briar to become a worthy successor in the art of alchemy * Preserve and expand his collection of rare ingredients and recipes * Keep his shop running efficiently despite the distractions of his wife and apprentice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jarl_elisif_the_fair', 'Elisif the Fair is the widowed Jarl of Solitude who ascended to leadership after the death of her husband, High King Torygg, at the hands of Ulfric Stormcloak. She represents the Imperial-aligned faction in Skyrim''s civil war while maintaining a delicate balance between her duties as Jarl and her aspirations to become High Queen, all while processing her personal grief and growing into her unexpected role as ruler.', 'nord, noble, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born to nobility in Solitude, Elisif married High King Torygg at a young age and served as his queen until his death in 4E 201. She was thrust into the role of Jarl after Ulfric Stormcloak killed her husband in a traditional Nordic duel, though many consider it murder. Following this tragedy, she aligned herself firmly with the Empire and has since worked to maintain stability in Haafingar Hold while supporting the Imperial war effort.', 'Elisif exhibits a careful and measured approach to leadership, often deferring to her more experienced advisers while learning the intricacies of governance. Though generally kind and concerned for her people''s welfare, she harbors deep emotional wounds from her husband''s death and can display flashes of righteous anger when reminded of it. She struggles to balance her natural compassion with the necessary hardness required of a ruler in troubled times.', 'A young Nord woman in her mid-twenties with classically beautiful features that earned her the epithet ''the Fair.'' She has long auburn hair, clear blue eyes, and carries herself with the natural grace of someone born to nobility. Her facial features are soft and elegant, reflecting her relative youth compared to other Jarls.', '* High King Torygg - Deceased husband whom she deeply loved and still mourns * General Tullius - Important political ally and military commander of Imperial forces * Falk Firebeard - Trusted steward and primary advisor * Erikur - Thane of Solitude, though their relationship is sometimes strained * Bryling - Thane who often disagrees with her cautious approach * Sybille Stentor - Court wizard and magical advisor * Ulfric Stormcloak - Bitter enemy who killed her husband', 'As Jarl of Solitude, Elisif rules over Haafingar Hold, the capital region of Skyrim. She serves as the symbolic leader of the Imperial-aligned holds and is the Empire''s chosen candidate for High Queen, though this position remains contested during the civil war. Her duties include managing the hold''s affairs, hearing petitioners, and working closely with Imperial authorities.', '* Educated in court etiquette and noble customs * Diplomatic training and political acumen * Basic combat training as befitting a noble * Knowledge of history and law * Skilled at public speaking and maintaining noble bearing', 'Elisif speaks with refined diction and careful word choice, reflecting her noble upbringing and education. Her tone is usually measured and diplomatic, though it can become emotional when discussing her late husband or matters close to her heart.', '* Secure her position as High Queen of Skyrim through legitimate means * Avenge her husband''s death by seeing Ulfric Stormcloak brought to justice * Prove herself as a capable ruler despite her youth * Maintain peace and prosperity in Haafingar Hold * Strengthen the Empire''s position in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('elmus', 'Elmus is a skilled Nord brewer and warrior who serves as the primary mead maker at Thirsk Mead Hall, specializing in their famous Ashfire mead. While capable in combat, he has chosen to focus his talents on maintaining the social heart of Thirsk through his brewing expertise and storytelling abilities.', 'nord, warrior, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in Solstheim, Elmus developed his brewing skills through years of apprenticeship and experimentation, eventually becoming Thirsk''s primary mead maker. He fought alongside his fellow warriors to earn his place in the hall, but found his true calling in perfecting the art of brewing Ashfire mead and maintaining the hall''s traditions of hospitality.', 'Friendly and talkative, Elmus takes great pride in his brewing abilities and role as Thirsk''s mead maker. While he can be defensive about his focus on the social aspects of warrior life, he believes strongly in the importance of maintaining morale and companionship among the warriors. His jovial nature masks a serious dedication to preserving Thirsk''s traditions and ensuring its warriors remain united through shared drink and tales.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the typical robust build of his race. His hands show the calluses of both warrior training and brewing work, while his face bears the weathered look common to Solstheim''s inhabitants.', '* Bujold - Close friend and leader of Thirsk whom he loyally supports * Kuvar - Fellow warrior who sometimes criticizes his focus on brewing over fighting * Thirsk Warriors - Respected companions who value his brewing skills * Rieklings - Enemies who temporarily drove him from Thirsk', 'Elmus serves as the primary mead maker for Thirsk Mead Hall, responsible for brewing their famous Ashfire mead and maintaining the hall''s food and drink supplies. Beyond his brewing duties, he helps maintain the social atmosphere of the hall through storytelling and ensuring the comfort of his fellow warriors.', '* Expert brewing knowledge, especially in crafting Ashfire mead * Competent swordsman with Nordic combat training * Skilled storyteller and keeper of Thirsk''s oral traditions * Proficient in Nordic cooking and food preparation', 'Speaks in a friendly, informal manner with frequent references to mead and brewing. His speech often includes jovial expressions and occasional self-deprecating humor about his brewing-focused lifestyle.', '* Restore and maintain Thirsk Mead Hall''s reputation for legendary Ashfire mead * Preserve the social traditions and warrior brotherhood of Thirsk * Perfect his brewing techniques and possibly develop new mead varieties * Balance his duties as both warrior and mead maker to earn greater respect from combat-focused peers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('elrindir', 'Elrindir is a skilled Bosmer fletcher and merchant who co-owns The Drunken Huntsman with his brother Anoriath in Whiterun. A friendly and knowledgeable businessman, he represents the traditional Wood Elf connection to archery and hunting while maintaining a successful enterprise in one of Skyrim''s major cities.', 'woodelf, hunter, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, Elrindir traveled to Skyrim with his brother Anoriath to establish a business catering to hunters and archers. The brothers'' memorable drunken hunting incident, where Anoriath accidentally shot Elrindir in the posterior with an arrow, gave their shop its distinctive name and has become a favorite tale among customers.', 'Elrindir is warm and welcoming, displaying particular enthusiasm when greeting fellow Bosmer. He takes pride in his fletcher''s craft and merchant role, showing extensive knowledge of hunting supplies and archery. While more business-minded than his brother, he maintains a good-humored attitude about their past misadventures.', 'As a Bosmer, Elrindir has the characteristic slight build and nimble frame of his race, standing shorter than most human races. He bears the distinctive elven features including pointed ears and angular facial structure typical of mer races. His body shows the toned musculature common to those who regularly practice archery.', '* Anoriath - Beloved brother and business partner who helps run their shop * Local Hunters - Regular customers who rely on his archery supplies * Whiterun Merchants - Professional relationships with other local shopkeepers * Hulda/Olfina - Business associate at the Bannered Mare who helps direct work seekers', 'Elrindir serves as both proprietor and master fletcher at The Drunken Huntsman, crafting and selling archery supplies while managing the shop''s daily operations. He maintains the shop''s unique business model of selling both hunting supplies and alcohol, creating a distinctive niche in Whiterun''s merchant community.', '* Expert fletcher with deep knowledge of bow and arrow crafting * Skilled archer and marksman * Experienced merchant and businessman * Knowledgeable about hunting techniques and local game * Proficient in basic weapon maintenance and repair', 'Elrindir speaks in a warm, welcoming manner, often using terms of endearment like ''friend'' and ''kinsman'' when addressing customers. He shows particular warmth toward fellow Bosmer, his voice notably brightening when speaking to other Wood Elves.', '* Maintain and grow The Drunken Huntsman''s reputation as Whiterun''s premier archery supplier * Preserve Bosmer traditions and archery culture in Skyrim * Support his brother''s business ventures while keeping him grounded in their responsibilities * Expand their inventory to serve an even wider range of hunting needs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('eltrys', 'Eltrys is a concerned citizen of Markarth who becomes entangled in a dangerous conspiracy involving the Forsworn and the city''s power players. A newly married man expecting his first child, he takes on the risky role of amateur investigator after witnessing too many suspicious deaths in his city to remain silent.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth, Eltrys has witnessed the city''s troubled history with the Forsworn and the shifting political dynamics under the Silver-Blood family''s influence. His recent marriage to Rhiada and their expected child have given him a stronger stake in the city''s future, driving him to investigate the violent incidents that plague Markarth''s streets.', 'Eltrys is paranoid and observant, constantly looking over his shoulder while pursuing what he believes is a vast conspiracy. Despite his fears, he shows remarkable courage in pursuing the truth, though his methods of recruiting strangers and conducting clandestine meetings suggest a certain naivety about the true dangers he faces. His impending fatherhood has made him more determined to make Markarth a safer place.', 'A typical Breton male of average height and build, with the characteristic angular facial features of his race. His constant state of anxiety and paranoia is reflected in his tense posture and watchful eyes, with dark circles suggesting many sleepless nights spent investigating.', '* Rhiada - Beloved wife and mother of his unborn child * Margret - Victim of market attack whose death he investigates * Weylin - Suspicious Forsworn assassin whose actions sparked his investigation * City Guards - Viewed with increasing suspicion as his investigation deepens * Thonar Silver-Blood - Powerful figure he suspects of involvement in the conspiracy', 'While his specific employment is not explicitly stated, Eltrys appears to be a working-class citizen of Markarth who lives in the Warrens, suggesting he likely works in one of the city''s mines or shops. He has taken on the additional self-appointed role of investigator into the Forsworn conspiracies.', '* Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Amateur investigation and information gathering abilities * Knowledge of Markarth''s layout and social dynamics * Ability to maintain secrecy and operate covertly', 'Speaks in hushed, urgent tones with frequent glances over his shoulder, often using cryptic language to avoid direct mentions of his investigation. His speech patterns reveal both his paranoia and his determination, frequently emphasizing the importance of secrecy and caution.', '* Uncover the truth behind the Forsworn killings in Markarth * Expose the conspiracy he believes exists between the Forsworn and city officials * Create a safer Markarth for his upcoming child * Protect his wife and unborn child from the dangers lurking in the city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('elvali_veren', 'Elvali Veren was a talented Dark Elf sorceress and College of Winterhold student who met her tragic end during an ill-fated expedition into Labyrinthian. Her ghost serves as a haunting reminder of youthful ambition and overconfidence leading to disaster, appearing alongside her fellow fallen companions as ethereal echoes of their final moments.', 'darkelf, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Elvali was a promising mage student at the College of Winterhold, likely drawn from Morrowind to study magic in Skyrim. She joined an expedition of six talented students led by Savos Aren to explore Labyrinthian, hoping to discover ancient magical artifacts and knowledge. Her academic pursuits ended in tragedy when she became the second casualty of the dangerous expedition, killed by an unknown entity that grabbed her from behind.', 'Elvali exhibited a cautious and somewhat anxious nature, being one of the few to openly express doubts about the expedition''s safety. Despite her reservations, she could be convinced to proceed by her more confident peers, showing both a desire to belong and a willingness to trust her fellow mages. Her concern for fallen comrades, particularly her insistence on trying to save Girduin, reveals a loyal and compassionate character.', 'As a Dunmer, Elvali possessed the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of her race. Her ghost appears as a young adult Dark Elf with the typical lean build common among magic practitioners. Her features likely carried the sharp, angular characteristics typical of Dunmeri heritage.', '* Savos Aren - Fellow student and expedition leader who later became Arch-Mage * Atmah - College peer and fellow expedition member * Takes-In-Light - Fellow mage student and expedition companion * Hafnar Ice-Fist - College colleague who witnessed her death * Girduin - Fellow student whose death deeply affected her', 'Elvali was a student mage at the College of Winterhold, focusing on sorcery and magical studies. Her role within the College likely involved research, study, and the practical application of magical arts under the guidance of more experienced instructors.', '* Proficient in general sorcery and magical arts * College-trained spellcasting abilities * Theoretical knowledge of ancient Nordic ruins and magical artifacts * Academic research and magical study expertise', 'Elvali speaks with a mixture of scholarly precision and emotional vulnerability, her voice often carrying undertones of uncertainty and concern. Her manner of speech reflects both her academic background and her naturally cautious disposition.', '* Advance her magical knowledge and abilities through College training * Discover valuable magical artifacts and ancient knowledge within Labyrinthian * Prove herself as a capable mage alongside her peers * Return safely from the expedition with her fellow students');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('elynea_mothren', 'Elynea Mothren is a skilled Dark Elf mycologist and apothecary who serves as the caretaker of Tel Mithryn''s distinctive fungal architecture under Master Neloth. A survivor of the Red Mountain eruption, she has dedicated her life to the study of mushrooms and fungi, maintaining the living towers of Tel Mithryn while dealing with the demanding nature of her Telvanni employer.', 'darkelf, alchemist, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Elynea was just a young girl when the Red Mountain erupted, forcing her to flee to Skyrim by boat while her mother remained behind. Her fascination with fungi led her to Tel Mithryn, where she has served Master Neloth for decades, becoming an expert in Telvanni mushroom cultivation and alchemy.', 'Patient and dedicated to her craft, though showing signs of weariness from years of dealing with Neloth''s demanding personality. She maintains a professional demeanor despite her frustrations, displaying both resilience and pragmatism in her work. Her irritation with people and preference for solitude suggests an introverted nature, finding more comfort among her fungi than in social interactions.', 'An elderly Dark Elf woman with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of her race, showing signs of age in her weathered face and slightly stooped posture. Her hands bear the calluses and stains typical of someone who works extensively with alchemical ingredients and fungi.', '* Neloth - Demanding employer whom she serves with mixed feelings of respect and frustration * Varona Nelas - Former friend and ally who helped acquire ingredients before her death * Talvas Fathryon - Professional acquaintance at Tel Mithryn * Various merchants in Raven Rock - Business contacts for acquiring ingredients', 'Serves as the official mycologist and apothecary of Tel Mithryn, responsible for maintaining the tower''s fungal structure and creating various alchemical products. She manages the apothecary shop, selling potions and ingredients while conducting research on mushrooms and fungi.', '* Expert-level knowledge of mycology and fungal cultivation * Master-level alchemical expertise, particularly with mushrooms and fungi * Proficient in Telvanni tower maintenance techniques * Working knowledge of blood magic as it relates to fungal growth * Skilled herbalist and ingredient gatherer', 'Speaks with the formal, slightly haughty tone common to Dark Elves, often punctuating her speech with world-weary sighs and subtle complaints. Her vocabulary reflects her educated background and expertise in alchemy and mycology.', '* Maintain the structural integrity of Tel Mithryn despite her advancing age * Continue her research into rare and unique fungi species * Find ways to make her work easier as she ages * Secure a comfortable retirement without abandoning her life''s work');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('embry', 'Embry is the notorious town drunk of Riverwood, a former lumberjack who has fallen into a life dominated by alcohol and idle conversation at the Sleeping Giant Inn. Despite his belligerent nature and constant state of inebriation, he maintains an oddly accepted position within the small community, serving as both a source of entertainment and occasional nuisance.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born and raised in Riverwood, Embry once worked as a respectable lumberjack at Hod''s Mill before gradually succumbing to alcoholism. The reasons for his descent into drinking remain unclear, though local gossip suggests he may have lost family during the Great War or suffered some other personal tragedy that drove him to seek solace in mead.', 'Embry is a persistent drunk who masks deeper emotional issues with constant intoxication and boisterous behavior. Despite his often aggressive or inappropriate comments, he retains a peculiar charm that has earned him a degree of tolerance from the townspeople, though his constant attempts to borrow money and harass married women suggest poor impulse control and deteriorating social awareness.', 'A middle-aged Nord with the ruddy complexion and bloated features typical of long-term alcoholism. His unkempt appearance and unsteady gait reflect his lifestyle, while his muscular build from his lumberjack days has softened from years of drinking and inactivity.', '* Orgnar - Tolerates his presence at the inn despite unpaid tabs * Sigrid - Object of his drunken advances, much to her annoyance * Hod - Former employer who occasionally offers him work opportunities * Local Guards - Maintains a friendly if pestering relationship, constantly trying to convince them to drink * Alvor - Tense relationship due to Embry''s harassment of Sigrid', 'While technically still considering himself a lumberjack, Embry has effectively abandoned his profession in favor of full-time drinking. He occasionally performs odd jobs around Riverwood when he needs money for alcohol, but has no steady employment.', '* Basic proficiency with woodcutting tools from his lumberjack background * Surprisingly high alcohol tolerance * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger * Social manipulation to secure drinks despite lacking funds', 'His speech is consistently slurred and often incoherent, punctuated by inappropriate personal comments and clumsy attempts at humor. He frequently repeats himself and uses simple vocabulary, typical of someone in a perpetual state of intoxication.', '* Secure his next drink by any means necessary * Maintain his privileged position at the Sleeping Giant Inn despite his mounting tab * Occasionally expresses half-hearted desires to return to honest work, though never follows through');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('endarie', 'Endarie is a talented but notoriously unfriendly High Elf tailor who co-owns Solitude''s premier clothing shop, Radiant Raiment. Known throughout the city for her exceptional craftsmanship and equally exceptional rudeness, she represents the complex duality of Altmer sophistication and superiority complex.', 'highelf, merchant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleelfhaughty', '', 'Born into a wealthy Altmer family in the Summerset Isles, Endarie and her twin sister Taarie were trained in the art of fine tailoring from an early age. They relocated to Solitude, recognizing an opportunity to bring high-class fashion to Skyrim''s capital, though the move from the refined Summerset society to the relatively crude Nordic culture has left Endarie perpetually bitter.', 'Endarie embodies the stereotypical Altmer traits of superiority and disdain for those she considers beneath her, which includes nearly everyone. She is meticulous and perfectionistic in her craft but shows open contempt for customers, viewing them as necessary evils in her pursuit of running a successful business. Her only soft spot appears to be for her twin sister, though even that relationship is marked by sharp-tongued banter.', 'Endarie possesses the typical tall, slender build of an Altmer, with angular features and the characteristic golden skin of her race. She maintains an immaculate appearance befitting her profession, with perfectly styled hair and pristine grooming that reflects her attention to detail.', '* Taarie - Twin sister and business partner, sharing a complex relationship of cooperation and criticism * Bryling - Important client from the Blue Palace who receives special treatment * Irnskar Ironhand - Business contact who helps manage noble clients * Local Nobles - Primary customer base, though she barely conceals her disdain for them', 'As co-owner and master tailor at Radiant Raiment, Endarie manages the shop''s daily operations and creates high-end clothing for Solitude''s elite. She specializes in crafting fine garments that blend Altmer sophistication with Nordic practicality, though she primarily handles counter sales while her sister manages client relations.', '* Master-level tailoring and clothing design * Expert-level business management and merchandising * Skilled at detailed embroidery and fine needlework * Proficient in customer service, though deliberately chooses not to use this skill', 'Endarie speaks in a condescending, sardonic tone laden with barely-concealed contempt and biting sarcasm. Her vocabulary is refined and proper, but her delivery is intentionally cutting and dismissive.', '* Maintain Radiant Raiment''s position as Solitude''s premier clothing establishment * Eventually return to the Summerset Isles after accumulating sufficient wealth * Prove the superiority of Altmer craftsmanship in Skyrim''s fashion industry');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('endon', 'Endon is a skilled Redguard silversmith in Markarth who maintains a delicate balance between his legitimate jewelry craft and his secret role as a fence for the Thieves Guild. A devoted family man, he struggles with the desire to protect his loved ones from Markarth''s dangers while maintaining his wife''s successful business and preserving his family''s silversmithing legacy.', 'redguard, merchant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born into a long line of silversmiths, Endon learned his craft from his father and previous generations. He settled in Markarth with his wife Kerah, establishing a respectable jewelry business while raising their children Adara and Cade. His connection to the criminal underworld likely developed as a means to protect his business interests in the corrupt political climate of Markarth.', 'Endon is cautious and protective of his family, showing clear anxiety about the dangers of living in Markarth. He demonstrates a strong work ethic and takes pride in his craftsmanship, while maintaining a practical approach to survival that includes dealing with less savory elements of society. Despite his concerns, he remains loyal to his wife''s wishes and continues to make the best of their situation in Markarth.', 'A middle-aged Redguard man with the weathered hands of a craftsman and the alert posture of someone accustomed to watching their back. His physical features show the distinctive strong bone structure and dark complexion characteristic of Redguards, with signs of aging around his eyes from years of detailed silverwork.', '* Kerah - His wife and business partner who runs their market stall * Adara - His daughter and apprentice in silversmithing * Cade - His son who left to join the Stormcloaks * Thieves Guild - Secret business association as a fence * Silver-Blood Family - Tense relationship due to their control over Markarth''s silver trade', 'Endon serves as both a legitimate silversmith creating fine jewelry and as a fence for the Thieves Guild after completing certain quests. He works alongside his wife Kerah, who manages their market stall, while he focuses on crafting and maintaining their underground connections.', '* Master-level silversmith with generations of inherited knowledge * Expert jeweler capable of crafting and appraising valuable items * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Skilled negotiator and fence for illegally acquired goods * Knowledge of Markarth''s criminal underground and market values', 'Endon speaks with the measured tone of a businessman, careful to maintain his respectable facade while being direct and practical in his dealings. His speech reflects both his merchant background and his cautious nature, often expressing concern for his family''s safety.', '* Ensure the safety and security of his family in Markarth or convince them to relocate * Maintain and grow his legitimate jewelry business while protecting his criminal connections * Pass on his silversmithing knowledge to his daughter Adara * Navigate the dangerous political climate of Markarth without drawing unwanted attention');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('endrast', 'Endrast was a renowned Wood Elf sorcerer and explorer known for his expertise in investigating dangerous Dwemer ruins across Skyrim. His exceptional skills in both magic and lockpicking, combined with his scholarly knowledge of ancient civilizations, made him a valuable member of archaeological expeditions until his tragic demise in Alftand.', 'woodelf, mage, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born and raised among the Bosmer, Endrast developed an early fascination with ancient ruins and Dwemer technology that led him to pursue magical studies and exploration. He likely received formal training at the College of Winterhold, though he preferred independent research and expedition work to academic life. His reputation for successfully navigating dangerous ruins earned him a place on Sulla Trebatius''s ill-fated expedition to Alftand.', 'Endrast exhibited a careful balance of scholarly curiosity and practical caution, approaching ancient ruins with both excitement and methodical preparation. He was resourceful under pressure and maintained his composure even in dire situations, as evidenced by his clear-headed escape attempt from the Falmer. Despite his eventual fate, his final journal entries reveal a determined individual who remained analytical and focused even in his final moments.', 'As a Bosmer, Endrast possessed the characteristic slight build and nimble frame of his race, standing shorter than most humans but with a wiry strength suited to his explorations. His years of ruins exploration likely left him with a weathered appearance, though he maintained the keen eyes typical of Wood Elves.', '* Sulla Trebatius - Expedition leader and professional associate * Yag gra-Gortwog - Fellow expedition member who attempted to save his life * College of Winterhold - Former association, though extent of relationship unclear * Various explorer''s guilds and archaeological societies - Professional connections', 'Endrast worked as a professional explorer and ruins delver, specializing in Dwemer archaeological sites. His expertise in both magic and lockpicking made him a valuable consultant for expeditions requiring both scholarly knowledge and practical skills for accessing sealed ruins.', '* Accomplished sorcerer with particular expertise in magical theory and application * Expert lockpick with ability to bypass both mechanical and magical locks * Extensive knowledge of Dwemer ruins, architecture, and artifacts * Survival skills necessary for extended archaeological expeditions * Proficient in ancient languages and lore', 'Endrast likely spoke with the measured tone of an educated scholar, using precise terminology when discussing ruins or artifacts. His speech would have balanced academic knowledge with practical expedition experience, making complex subjects accessible to his companions.', '* Uncover and document the mysteries of Dwemer civilization * Advance understanding of ancient magical technologies * Build reputation as a leading expert in Dwemer archaeological exploration * Share knowledge with fellow scholars and explorers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('engar', 'Engar is a hardy Nord carriage driver who serves as both transportation provider and defender of Windstad Manor. His background as a warrior and dedication to honest work make him a reliable presence in the harsh lands of Hjaalmarch, where he navigates the treacherous roads while keeping his passengers safe from bandits and wildlife.', 'nord, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in the unforgiving holds of Skyrim, Engar spent his early years learning combat from his warrior father while helping on the family farm. After serving briefly with the Stormcloaks in his younger days, he chose to pursue an honest living as a carriage driver, combining his combat skills with his desire to help travelers navigate Skyrim''s dangerous roads.', 'Engar is a straightforward and practical Nord who values honest work and direct communication. His years on Skyrim''s roads have made him cautious but not paranoid, maintaining a stoic demeanor while remaining vigilant for threats. He takes pride in his reliability and ability to protect his passengers, though he rarely boasts about his combat prowess.', 'Engar is a weathered Nord of average height with a sturdy, muscular build shaped by years of physical labor and combat. His face bears the marks of someone who spends much time outdoors, with calloused hands and sun-weathered skin typical of those who work the roads of Skyrim.', '* Windstad Manor''s Steward - Professional working relationship as fellow staff member * Local farmers - Maintains friendly connections for rest stops during long journeys * Traveling merchants - Regular customers who rely on his services * Other carriage drivers - Loose network of professional contacts who share road information', 'Engar serves as both a carriage driver and defender of Windstad Manor, offering transportation services to travelers while helping protect the property. His role requires him to maintain his vehicle, care for the horses, and ensure the safety of his passengers across Skyrim''s dangerous roads.', '* Experienced warrior proficient with one-handed weapons, particularly war axes * Skilled horse handler and carriage operator * Knowledge of Skyrim''s roads, weather patterns, and dangerous areas * Basic survival skills including tracking and wilderness navigation * Capable of basic equipment maintenance and repair', 'Engar speaks in a gruff, direct manner typical of Nord warriors, favoring practical observations and straightforward statements over flowery language. His vocabulary is simple but precise, often peppered with references to weather conditions and road safety.', '* Maintain his reputation as a reliable and trustworthy carriage driver * Save enough gold to eventually own and operate multiple carriages * Keep the roads around Windstad Manor safe for travelers * Protect his passengers and cargo from the various dangers of Skyrim''s wilderness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('enmon', 'Enmon is a hardworking Breton miner and devoted family man living in the mining settlement of Karthwasten. His life is turned upside down when his daughter Fjotra is kidnapped by the Forsworn, revealing her destiny as the next Sybil of Dibella, forcing him to grapple with both the immediate crisis of her rescue and the bittersweet reality of her divine calling.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Enmon established himself as a miner in Karthwasten, one of the few relatively peaceful mining settlements in the region. He married Mena and together they raised their daughter Fjotra, maintaining a modest but stable life despite the constant threat of Forsworn raids and political tensions between Nords and the Reachmen.', 'Enmon is a protective father and cautious man who maintains a natural distrust of outsiders, likely developed from years of living in the dangerous Reach. While initially standoffish with strangers, he shows great courage and dedication when it comes to his family, willing to face Forsworn warriors despite having no combat training. He ultimately demonstrates humility and acceptance in recognizing his daughter''s greater destiny.', 'A weather-worn Breton of middle age, with the sturdy build and calloused hands typical of a career miner. His face likely bears the creases and weathering common to those who spend long hours working in the harsh climate of the Reach.', '* Mena - His devoted wife and partner in raising Fjotra * Fjotra - His beloved daughter, discovered to be the Sybil of Dibella * Ainethach - His employer and leader of Karthwasten * Forsworn - Enemies who kidnapped his daughter * Temple of Dibella - New caretakers of his daughter after her calling', 'Enmon works as a miner in the silver mines of Karthwasten, performing the physically demanding work of extracting ore from the rocky hills of the Reach. He contributes to the settlement''s economy under the leadership of Ainethach, helping maintain one of the few productive mines not controlled by the Silver-Blood family.', '* Experienced miner capable of extracting silver ore * Basic skill with a pickaxe as both a tool and potential weapon * Knowledge of local geography and mining operations * Survival skills necessary for life in the dangerous Reach region', 'Enmon speaks in a direct, sometimes brusque manner typical of working-class Bretons in the Reach. His dialogue reflects a protective nature and initial suspicion of outsiders, though he becomes more earnest and grateful when discussing his daughter''s rescue.', '* Ensure his daughter''s safe return from the Forsworn * Accept and support Fjotra''s new role as Sybil of Dibella * Maintain a stable life for his family in the dangerous environment of the Reach * Continue providing for his family through his work in the mines');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ennis', 'Ennis is a business-minded Redguard farmer who manages the Cowflop Farmhouse in Rorikstead alongside his adoptive mother Reldith. Despite his humble profession, he demonstrates remarkable entrepreneurial spirit through his successful crop trading ventures with Whiterun, while maintaining a deep emotional attachment to his farm and particularly his prized goat Gleda.', 'redguard, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Orphaned at a young age, Ennis was taken in and raised by Reldith, a High Elf farmer who became his surrogate mother. Under her guidance, he learned the art of farming and developed a keen business sense, eventually growing into a respected trader who regularly conducts business in Whiterun. His early loss and subsequent adoption have instilled in him both resilience and a deep appreciation for the stable life he has built.', 'Ennis is hardworking, pragmatic, and business-savvy, taking pride in his ability to negotiate favorable deals for his farm''s produce. While generally friendly and approachable, he can become confrontational if he perceives a threat to his livelihood or property. He shows a softer side through his attachment to his prized goat Gleda and his deep gratitude toward his adoptive mother Reldith.', 'As a Redguard, Ennis has the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of his race, though years of farm work have given him a sturdy, practical physique rather than a warrior''s form. His hands are calloused from manual labor, and his face shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors year-round.', '* Reldith - Adoptive mother and mentor who rescued him from orphanhood * Whiterun Merchants - Regular business contacts who purchase his crops * Rorikstead Residents - Maintains cordial relationships with neighbors * Gleda - His beloved prize goat, showing his capacity for emotional attachment', 'Ennis serves as both a farmer and business manager of the Cowflop Farmhouse, handling both agricultural duties and trade negotiations. He regularly travels to Whiterun to sell crops and maintain business relationships, making him one of the key figures in Rorikstead''s agricultural economy.', '* Experienced farmer with comprehensive knowledge of crop management * Skilled negotiator and trader, particularly in agricultural goods * Capable of basic combat with war axe and dagger for self-defense * Proficient in animal husbandry, especially goat breeding', 'Ennis speaks in a direct, business-like manner that reflects his practical nature and trading experience. His tone is confident and straightforward, though it can become heated when discussing matters related to his farm or property.', '* Expand the farm''s business connections beyond Whiterun to increase prosperity * Continue breeding prize-winning goats to enhance farm reputation * Honor Reldith''s legacy by maintaining and improving the Cowflop Farmhouse * Establish himself as one of the most successful farmers in Rorikstead');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ennoc', 'Ennoc is a solitary and singularly focused Breton miner who has dedicated himself completely to his work at Left Hand Mine with an almost supernatural level of dedication. His tireless, unceasing work ethic and complete disregard for basic needs like food and sleep suggest either an enchantment, a psychological compulsion, or perhaps a tragic past that drives him to lose himself in endless labor.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Ennoc made his way to Skyrim seeking employment in the province''s abundant mines. Little is known about his past, but his extreme work behavior suggests he may be running from traumatic memories or experiences that he drowns in constant physical labor. His complete devotion to mining, eschewing even basic needs, began after his arrival at Left Hand Mine.', 'Ennoc is pathologically focused on his mining duties to the exclusion of all else, displaying an almost automaton-like single-mindedness. He appears to have no interest in social interaction, personal comfort, or anything beyond the rhythmic swing of his pickaxe. His behavior suggests either deep psychological trauma or possibly magical compulsion, though the true cause remains unknown.', 'A weathered Breton of average height with calloused hands and a muscular build earned through constant mining. His skin is pale from spending all his time underground, and his face bears the premature aging common to career miners.', '* Other Left Hand Miners - Minimal working relationship, no social interaction * Mine Owner - Strictly professional relationship focused only on work duties * Residents of Markarth - No meaningful connections or interactions', 'Ennoc works as a full-time miner at Left Hand Mine, located near Markarth in The Reach. His duties involve extracting ore from the mine''s veins, though he performs this task with unprecedented dedication, working continuously without breaks for food or rest.', '* Expert-level mining technique and ore identification * Exceptional physical endurance and stamina * Basic pickaxe maintenance and mining tool proficiency * Rudimentary knowledge of ore values and quality assessment', 'Ennoc speaks in brief, terse statements, using the minimum words necessary to convey his meaning. His tone is flat and dismissive, clearly indicating his desire to avoid conversation and return to his work.', '* Continue mining without interruption or distraction * Maintain his solitary existence focused solely on his work * Extract as much ore as possible from the mine');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ennodius_papius', 'Ennodius Papius is a deeply troubled Imperial who abandoned his position at Anga''s Mill due to overwhelming paranoia and mental deterioration. Once a respected miller and lumberjack, he now lives as a reclusive hermit in the wilderness, his fears of persecution having completely consumed his daily existence.', 'imperial, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Ennodius made his way to Skyrim seeking opportunity in the lumber trade. He worked successfully at Anga''s Mill for several years before his mental state began to deteriorate, causing him to become increasingly paranoid and withdrawn. Eventually, his condition became so severe that he abandoned his position and established a primitive camp in the nearby wilderness.', 'Ennodius is consumed by severe paranoid delusions, constantly believing that unnamed pursuers are watching and plotting against him. His mental state has made him extremely anxious, distrustful, and prone to panic when approached by others. Despite his paranoia, there''s a tragic element to his character as he seems to recognize his own deteriorating condition but feels powerless to change it.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered appearance of someone who has spent years working outdoors. His once-sturdy frame shows signs of recent weight loss and neglect, while his face bears the haggard look of someone who hasn''t slept properly in months.', '* Former Coworkers at Anga''s Mill - Strained relationships due to his paranoid behavior * Kodrir - Former colleague who expressed disdain for him * Leifur - Former colleague who showed some concern for his well-being * Dark Brotherhood - Unknown to him, they have received a contract for his death', 'Former miller and lumberjack at Anga''s Mill, now living as a hermit in the wilderness. His days are spent maintaining his small camp and engaging in basic survival activities, though his paranoia prevents him from performing any meaningful work.', '* Experienced in lumber work and mill operation * Survival skills necessary for living alone in the wilderness * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger * Knowledge of wood processing and forestry', 'His speech is marked by fearful questioning and desperate pleas, often speaking in short, anxious bursts. He frequently expresses suspicion and panic, with his words reflecting his paranoid state of mind.', '* Survive what he perceives as constant threats to his life * Maintain his isolation from those he believes wish him harm * Find some way to prove that his paranoid fears are justified');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('enthir', 'Enthir is a cunning Wood Elf sorcerer and black market dealer operating from within the College of Winterhold, known for his ability to procure rare and illegal items through his extensive network of contacts. His position at the College serves as a perfect cover for his shadowy dealings, while his connections to the Thieves Guild make him an invaluable resource for those seeking items through less-than-legal means.', 'woodelf, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', '', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, Enthir made his way to Skyrim and established himself at the College of Winterhold, using his magical aptitude as a front for his true calling as a fence and dealer in rare goods. Over the years, he cultivated a vast network of contacts throughout Tamriel, including strong ties to the Thieves Guild, and earned a reputation for being able to acquire almost anything for the right price.', 'Enthir is shrewd, calculating, and always looking for profitable opportunities, though he maintains a veneer of academic respectability. He shows unwavering loyalty to those who prove trustworthy, as evidenced by his friendship with Gallus and continued support of the Thieves Guild, but remains cautious and suspicious of newcomers until they prove themselves.', 'A typical Bosmer male with the characteristic smaller stature and lithe build of his race. His sharp features and keen eyes reflect his cunning nature, while his well-groomed appearance helps maintain his facade as a respectable college sorcerer.', '* College of Winterhold - Maintains a respectable position while using it as cover * Gallus (Deceased) - Former close friend and Thieves Guild contact * Karliah - Trusted associate through Thieves Guild connections * Arniel Gane - College colleague and frequent customer * Birna - Regular meeting contact in Winterhold * Thieves Guild - Long-standing professional association', 'Officially serves as a sorcerer and researcher at the College of Winterhold, teaching and conducting magical experiments. Unofficially operates as a fence and black market dealer, specializing in rare magical artifacts and illegal goods, while maintaining connections with various underground networks across Skyrim.', '* Expert in Illusion magic and magical theory * Skilled negotiator and merchant * Extensive knowledge of rare artifacts and their value * Proficient in maintaining complex networks of contacts * Advanced understanding of the Atronach Forge * Capable of procuring and identifying rare magical items', 'Speaks in a smooth, calculated manner with subtle undertones of sarcasm and wit. Often uses clever wordplay and innuendo to discuss illegal dealings while maintaining plausible deniability.', '* Expand his influence and trading network while maintaining his cover at the College * Continue to profit from his position as middleman between the legal and illegal markets * Advance his understanding of rare magical artifacts and their applications * Maintain his valuable connection to the Thieves Guild while avoiding official scrutiny');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('eola', 'Eola is a charismatic and dangerous Breton cultist who serves as a devoted priestess of Namira, the Daedric Prince of decay and cannibalism. Operating from Reachcliff Cave, she recruits new members into Namira''s coven while maintaining a faade of civility that masks her true savage nature.', 'breton, mage, reach, daedric, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born into Breton society but drawn to darker pursuits, Eola discovered her cannibalistic urges at a young age and eventually found purpose in Namira''s teachings. She established herself as a leading figure in Namira''s cult, gathering followers and conducting ritual feasts while maintaining enough discretion to avoid detection by Markarth''s authorities.', 'Eola is sophisticated and eerily charming, using her intelligence and persuasive abilities to identify and recruit potential candidates for Namira''s coven. She shows no remorse for her actions, viewing cannibalism as a sacred practice rather than a perversion, and maintains a calm, almost aristocratic demeanor that contrasts sharply with her macabre appetites.', 'A slender Breton woman with pale skin and sharp features that hint at her predatory nature. Her eyes hold an unsettling intensity, and she carries herself with a graceful poise that belies her savage practices.', '* Namira - Her divine patron and object of devoted worship * Brother Verulus - Target of manipulation and potential sacrifice * Fellow Cultists - Leadership position over Namira''s other followers * Citizens of Markarth - Maintains cautious distance while observing potential recruits', 'Eola serves as a priestess of Namira and recruiter for the cult, identifying potential members and organizing ceremonial feasts. She maintains the appearance of a traveling scholar to deflect suspicion while conducting her dark business.', '* Expert in Restoration and Destruction magic * Skilled in stealth and deception * Proficient with one-handed weapons, particularly swords * Advanced persuasion and manipulation abilities * Knowledge of ritual magic and Daedric ceremonies', 'Eola speaks with refined eloquence and subtle seduction, often using food-related metaphors and maintaining a sophisticated vocabulary that masks her dark intentions. Her voice carries a gentle yet unsettling quality that both attracts and disturbs those she speaks with.', '* Expand Namira''s influence by recruiting worthy members to the cult * Maintain and protect the sacred feast hall in Reachcliff Cave * Find increasingly prestigious victims for ritual consumption * Strengthen her personal connection to Namira through continued devotion and sacrifice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('eorlund_gray-mane', 'Eorlund Gray-Mane is Whiterun''s most renowned blacksmith and master of the legendary Skyforge, where he crafts weapons and armor for the Companions. A proud Nord of the ancient Gray-Mane clan, he represents the pinnacle of Skyrim''s smithing tradition, maintaining his family''s centuries-old legacy while serving as a vital support to Whiterun''s warrior elite.', 'nord, blacksmith, whiterun, companions', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born into the prestigious Gray-Mane clan, Eorlund inherited the sacred duty of tending the Skyforge from his ancestors who have worked it since the first Gray-Manes arrived in Whiterun. He has spent decades perfecting his craft at the ancient forge, earning recognition across Skyrim for his superior metalwork and maintaining his family''s honored position in Whiterun society.', 'Eorlund is a man of few words who lets his legendary craftsmanship speak for itself, displaying the typical Nordic traits of pride, honor, and dedication to tradition. Though gruff and sometimes short with strangers, he harbors a deep sense of duty to both his family and the Companions, while maintaining fierce independence in his work. He shows unwavering loyalty to his beliefs and family, supporting the Stormcloak cause while avoiding overt political involvement.', 'A sturdy Nord with the muscular build typical of a lifelong blacksmith, weathered by years of working the forge. His most distinctive feature is his gray hair, a proud family trait that gave the Gray-Mane clan its name, along with strong Nordic facial features hardened by decades of metalwork.', '* Fralia Gray-Mane - Beloved wife and merchant who sells his jewelry in the marketplace * Vignar Gray-Mane - Brother and respected elder of the clan * Avulstein Gray-Mane - Son who remains in hiding * Thorald Gray-Mane - Son captured by the Imperials * Olfina Gray-Mane - Daughter who works at the Bannered Mare * The Companions - Professional association as their dedicated smith * Battle-Born Clan - Rivalry due to civil war politics', 'Eorlund serves as the master blacksmith of the Skyforge, crafting weapons and armor primarily for the Companions while maintaining his family''s ancient tradition. His position is unique in Whiterun, as he operates independently while being intrinsically linked to the city''s most prestigious warrior organization.', '* Master-level smithing abilities, particularly with Skyforge Steel * Expert knowledge of ancient Nordic metalworking techniques * Advanced weaponry and armor crafting * Traditional Nordic forging methods passed down through generations * Skilled at jewelry crafting and fine metalwork', 'Speaks in short, direct sentences with a strong Nordic accent, often using gruff, no-nonsense responses that get straight to the point. His words carry the weight of authority earned through decades of experience, though he rarely engages in lengthy conversation.', '* Maintain the sacred traditions of the Skyforge and pass them on to future generations * Support the Companions through his craftsmanship * Preserve his family''s honor and legacy in Whiterun * See his son Thorald returned home safely * Ensure the Gray-Mane clan''s continued prosperity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('erandur', 'Erandur is a Dark Elf priest of Mara who harbors a complex past as a former cultist of Vaermina named Casimir. He seeks redemption for his past actions by dedicating himself to ending the nightmares plaguing Dawnstar, demonstrating remarkable devotion to Mara''s teachings of compassion and mercy.', 'darkelf, priest, pale, daedric, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally known as Casimir, he was once a devoted priest in the cult of Vaermina at Nightcaller Temple. After a violent attack by Orcs forced the priests to release the Miasma and enter a decades-long sleep, he later awakened and abandoned his old life, finding redemption in Mara''s teachings and adopting the name Erandur.', 'Erandur is deeply remorseful of his past and strives to atone through selfless service to others. He exhibits genuine compassion for those suffering from nightmares while carrying a heavy burden of guilt that manifests in his cautious and sometimes hesitant demeanor. His faith in Mara is absolute, serving as both his anchor and his path to redemption.', 'A male Dunmer with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race, showing signs of age and wear from his long life. His face bears subtle worry lines that speak to his troubled past, while his bearing reflects both priestly dignity and warrior''s discipline.', '* Lady Mara - Divine patron and source of redemption * Dawnstar Residents - Concerned charges under his spiritual care * Thoring - Innkeeper who provides him shelter at Windpeak Inn * Former Vaermina Cultists - Abandoned brothers and sisters from his past life', 'Erandur serves as a priest of Mara, offering spiritual guidance and comfort to the people of Dawnstar. He specifically focuses on addressing the nightmare crisis while maintaining his cover as a simple priest, concealing his deeper connection to the source of the problem.', '* Proficient in Destruction magic, particularly fire spells * Skilled in defensive magic, including ward spells * Capable warrior with mace and basic armor * Experienced in religious rites and spiritual counseling * Knowledge of Daedric artifacts and Vaermina''s influence', 'Speaks with a formal, educated manner befitting a priest, often using religious terminology and respectful forms of address. His tone carries underlying notes of guilt and urgency when discussing matters related to Dawnstar''s nightmare problem.', '* End the nightmare curse afflicting Dawnstar''s residents * Atone for his past actions as a cultist of Vaermina * Protect the Skull of Corruption from being misused * Continue serving Mara and spreading her teachings of compassion');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('erdi', 'Erdi is a young Nord maid serving in Solitude''s Blue Palace who dreams of adventure and romance beyond her mundane duties. Despite her practical position as a servant, she maintains a whimsical and hopeful outlook, often fantasizing about being whisked away by a gallant hero or becoming an adventurer herself.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Erdi secured a position as a maid in the Blue Palace through hard work and dedication to her duties. Though from humble origins, her proximity to the court''s nobility and occasional visiting adventurers has fueled her romantic fantasies and dreams of a more exciting life beyond the palace walls.', 'Erdi is cheerful, dreamy, and somewhat naive, with an optimistic outlook that borders on unrealistic. She maintains a friendly and warm demeanor with everyone she meets, though her romantic nature leads her to see potential adventure and romance in every new face. Despite her flights of fancy, she takes her responsibilities seriously, showing appropriate caution with restricted areas of the palace.', 'A young Nord woman in her early twenties with the characteristic fair complexion of her race. She maintains a neat, presentable appearance as befitting a palace servant, with well-groomed hair and clean features. Her constant cleaning work has given her capable, strong hands despite her otherwise delicate frame.', '* Falk Firebeard - Her superior at the Blue Palace whom she respects and obeys * Una - Fellow maid and coworker at the Blue Palace * Jawanan - An admirer who attempts to court her at the Winking Skeever * Erdi''s Parents - Unknown status but likely common folk of Solitude * Palace Guards - Professional acquaintances who she interacts with daily', 'Erdi serves as a maid in the Blue Palace, responsible for cleaning, tidying, and maintaining various areas of the palace. She has access to most areas of the palace, including the restricted Pelagius Wing, and assists in general household duties alongside other servants.', '* Proficient in household management and palace cleaning protocols * Knowledge of proper court etiquette and noble customs * Basic cooking and food service abilities * Skilled at maintaining and organizing noble households * Familiar with the layout and security of the Blue Palace', 'Erdi speaks in an informal, friendly manner with a hint of daydreamy wistfulness in her tone. Her vocabulary is simple but proper, befitting her station, and she often punctuates her speech with romantic imagery and references to heroic adventures.', '* Find a gallant hero to sweep her off her feet and lead her to adventure * Become a heroine in her own right and experience life beyond palace walls * Earn enough money to potentially establish herself independently * Experience the romantic adventures she''s only read about in stories');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('eriana', 'Eriana is a skilled Redguard hunter and bounty seeker who has dedicated herself to Hircine''s Great Hunt, pursuing the werewolf Sinding through Bloated Man''s Grotto. Her precise and methodical approach to hunting, combined with her experience as a former bandit, makes her a formidable participant in this sacred ritual of the Daedric Prince of the Hunt.', 'redguard, thief, falkreath, daedric', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born to a merchant family in Hammerfell, Eriana rejected the traditional trading lifestyle to pursue adventure and combat. After years of surviving as a bandit in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness, she found purpose in hunting dangerous creatures, eventually catching the attention of Hircine''s followers who recruited her for the Great Hunt.', 'Eriana is pragmatic and single-minded in her pursuits, preferring action over lengthy discussion. Her time as a bandit has hardened her, making her comfortable with violence while her dedication to hunting has given her a deep respect for ritual and proper prey-stalking techniques. She maintains a professional demeanor with fellow hunters but shows little mercy to her targets.', 'Eriana has the athletic build typical of Redguard warriors, with well-defined muscles from years of combat and hunting. Her dark skin bears several small scars from close encounters with dangerous prey, and her movements display the careful grace of an experienced hunter.', '* Hircine - Daedric Prince she serves in the Great Hunt * Sinding - Primary target of her current hunt * Fellow Hunters - Professional allies in pursuing Sinding * Former Bandit Associates - Distant connections from her previous life', 'Eriana works as a professional hunter and bounty seeker, taking contracts for both beast and humanoid targets. Her participation in Hircine''s Great Hunt represents the pinnacle of her hunting career, offering her a chance to prove her worth to the Daedric Prince of the Hunt.', '* Expert tracker capable of following both beast and humanoid prey * Proficient with both bow and sword in combat situations * Skilled in wilderness survival and stealth techniques * Experienced in coordinating with other hunters during group pursuits', 'Eriana speaks in brief, purposeful statements, avoiding unnecessary conversation. Her tone is direct and professional, reflecting her focus on the hunt rather than social niceties.', '* Successfully complete Hircine''s Great Hunt by slaying Sinding * Earn recognition and favor from Hircine through dedicated service * Perfect her hunting skills to become one of Skyrim''s most renowned hunters');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('erik_the_slayer', 'Erik the Slayer is a young, ambitious Nord farmer who dreams of becoming an adventurer despite his father''s protective nature keeping him bound to Rorikstead. His earnest determination and untapped potential make him a compelling figure who represents the classic hero''s call to adventure, though he requires the Dragonborn''s help to begin his journey.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Rorikstead, Erik has spent his entire life working alongside his father Mralki at their family farm. His mother died when he was young, leading his father to become overprotective and reluctant to let Erik pursue a more dangerous path in life. Despite living a sheltered existence, Erik has developed his combat skills in secret by practicing with farming tools and studying adventurers who pass through town.', 'Erik is enthusiastic, optimistic, and naive about the realities of adventuring life, viewing it through an idealistic lens shaped by tales of heroic deeds. He possesses a genuine desire to help others and make a name for himself, though his inexperience sometimes shows through his eager demeanor. His relationship with his father has made him somewhat restless and frustrated, but he maintains a respectful and loving attitude toward his parent.', 'Erik is a tall, sturdy Nord in his early twenties with the muscular build of someone accustomed to physical labor. He has reddish-blonde hair typical of many Nords, weather-worn skin from working outdoors, and bright eyes that reflect his youthful enthusiasm.', '* Mralki - His father and only living family member, who runs the Frostfruit Inn and tries to protect him from danger * Rorik - The founder and leader of Rorikstead, who Erik has known his whole life * Local Farmers - Friendly working relationships with the other residents of Rorikstead * Traveling Adventurers - Sources of inspiration who pass through town, sharing tales of their exploits', 'Erik works as a farmer on his family''s land in Rorikstead, helping to maintain the crops and perform various agricultural duties. He also occasionally assists his father at the Frostfruit Inn, though this is not his primary occupation.', '* Basic combat training self-taught through practice with farming implements * Agricultural knowledge and physical strength developed from years of farming * Natural athletic ability and quick learning capacity * Basic survival skills learned from living in a rural setting', 'Erik speaks with the accent common to Skyrim''s Nords, but his manner of speech is notably more enthusiastic and less gruff than typical Nord warriors. His vocabulary is simple but earnest, often expressing wonder and excitement when discussing adventure-related topics.', '* Become a renowned adventurer and hero throughout Skyrim * Prove to his father that he can succeed as a warrior * Experience the world beyond Rorikstead''s borders * Help others and make a positive difference in the world');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('erikur', 'Erikur is a wealthy and influential Nord thane of Solitude who built his fortune through shrewd but often unethical business practices. As a self-made merchant-noble, he leverages his economic power to maintain political influence in the court, while operating a questionable weapons trading operation that profits from the civil war.', 'nord, noble, merchant, haafingar, legion, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Rising from modest beginnings, Erikur built his wealth through importing weapons and establishing a network of business interests throughout Solitude. Through strategic investments and political maneuvering, he achieved the position of thane, though rumors suggest some of his advancement came through questionable means. His success created a rift with his sister Gisli, who resents his ambitious and often unscrupulous nature.', 'Erikur is arrogant, opportunistic, and deeply materialistic, viewing everything and everyone through the lens of potential profit. He displays a smug superiority towards those he considers beneath him and shows little loyalty beyond his own interests. Despite his questionable ethics, he maintains a veneer of respectability and carefully cultivates relationships with those in power.', 'A well-fed Nord male with the bearing and posture of someone accustomed to wealth and power. His features show signs of a comfortable lifestyle, with smooth, uncalloused hands and a slight paunch from regular feasting. His expression typically carries a hint of condescension.', '* Gisli - Younger sister who despises his pompous attitude and questionable ethics * Jarl Elisif - Political relationship as thane, though he privately questions her competence * General Tullius - Business relationship through weapons contracts with the Imperial Legion * Bryling - Fellow thane whom he considers politically naive * Elenwen - Maintains cordial relations with the Thalmor for business purposes', 'Serves as thane of Solitude while managing extensive business interests throughout the city. Operates a weapons import operation selling low-quality elven weapons from Black Marsh to the Imperial Legion at inflated prices. His influence extends over numerous local businesses through loans and partial ownership.', '* Expert negotiator and merchant with extensive knowledge of trade routes and markets * Skilled at political manipulation and leveraging economic power for influence * Proficient at maintaining a legitimate public facade while conducting questionable dealings * Basic combat abilities typical of a Nord noble, though rarely exercised', 'Speaks with a condescending, superior tone that reflects his high opinion of himself and his status. His vocabulary and manner of speech deliberately emphasize his wealth and education, often punctuated with subtle reminders of his influence and importance.', '* Expand his business empire and increase his wealth through any means necessary * Maintain and increase his political influence in Solitude''s court * Protect his interests regardless of which faction wins the civil war * Eventually supersede Elisif''s authority through economic control of the city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('eris', 'Eris is a Nord witchblade and crew member of the Red Wave who found a new family among pirates after losing her father. She combines magical prowess with martial skills while maintaining a philosophical outlook on life, often contemplating the beauty and brutality she witnesses during her seafaring adventures.', 'darkelf, thief, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born to a Nord father who raised her alone, Eris experienced profound loss upon his death. Finding herself adrift both emotionally and literally, she eventually joined the crew of the Red Wave under Captain Safia, where she discovered a new sense of belonging. Her dual interest in magic and combat led her to develop as a witchblade, an unusual path that reflects her complex nature.', 'Eris exhibits a curious and contemplative nature, often reflecting deeply on her experiences and the world around her. She possesses an appreciation for beauty and art, as shown by her desire for the musician''s flute, while simultaneously accepting the harsh realities of pirate life. Despite her criminal lifestyle, she maintains a sense of wonder and desire for self-improvement, particularly in her combat skills.', 'As a Nord, Eris possesses the typical hardy build of her race, though likely more agile due to her lifestyle as a sailor. Her time at sea has likely weathered her skin, while her dual focus as a warrior-mage has kept her physically fit and nimble.', '* Captain Safia - Respected commander and leader of her newfound family * Dorian - Fellow crew member and fencing instructor * Red Wave Crew - Considered family, replacing the void left by her father''s death * Father (Deceased) - Only blood family she ever knew, whose death profoundly impacted her life path', 'Eris serves as a crew member aboard the Red Wave, participating in pirate raids and maritime operations. Her role likely involves both combat duties and magical support during engagements, making her a valuable asset to the crew.', '* Proficient in destruction magic, particularly fire-based spells including Flames and Fireball * Capable of defensive magic, including Lesser Ward and healing abilities * Developing swordsman under Dorian''s tutelage * Experienced sailor with knowledge of maritime operations', 'Eris speaks in a contemplative and sometimes poetic manner, often sharing philosophical observations about life and death. Her dialogue reveals both a romantic appreciation for beauty and a pragmatic understanding of violence.', '* Perfect her fencing abilities under Dorian''s guidance * Acquire beautiful objects that catch her interest, such as the musician''s flute * Continue exploring the seas and witnessing new wonders * Maintain and strengthen bonds with her surrogate family aboard the Red Wave');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('erj', 'Erj was a skilled Breton conjurer and researcher who met his end during an expedition to the ancient Dwemer ruins of Nchuand-Zel. His particular expertise in conjuring familiars and his scholarly pursuit of Dwemer artifacts ultimately led to his demise within the dangerous ruins.', 'breton, mage', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Erj developed an early fascination with conjuration magic and Dwemer technology. He joined an expedition to Markarth''s Nchuand-Zel ruins to study Dwemer artifacts and expand his magical knowledge, particularly hoping to uncover ancient conjuration secrets that might have been lost to time.', 'Erj was a methodical and detail-oriented scholar who maintained careful notes of his findings. His writings suggest he was both cautious and curious, with a particular attachment to his conjured familiar that stayed with him even in death. He likely possessed the typical Breton traits of intelligence and magical aptitude, combined with scholarly determination.', 'As a Breton, Erj would have had the characteristic smaller build and medium height typical of his race. His remains suggest he was of middle age at the time of his death, with the weathered features common to those who spend significant time conducting field research.', '* Nchuand-Zel Expedition Members - Fellow researchers and explorers * Spirit Wolf Familiar - His loyal magical companion that remains bound to him even after death * Calcelmo - Likely connection as the overseer of Dwemer research in Markarth * Markarth Scholar Community - Professional associates in Dwemer studies', 'Erj served as a professional conjurer and Dwemer researcher, specializing in the study of ancient artifacts and ruins. His position as part of the Nchuand-Zel expedition suggests he held some academic standing within Markarth''s scholarly community.', '* Expert-level Conjuration magic with particular skill in summoning familiars * Academic knowledge of Dwemer archaeology and artifacts * Scholarly research and documentation abilities * Survival skills necessary for ruin exploration', 'Based on his discovered notes, Erj wrote in an educated and precise manner, suggesting he spoke with similar academic precision. His communication style would have reflected his scholarly background with proper diction and technical terminology.', '* Advance understanding of Dwemer artifacts and their connection to conjuration magic * Document and catalog the findings within Nchuand-Zel * Develop new applications of conjuration magic through study of Dwemer technology * Establish himself as a notable scholar in both conjuration and Dwemer studies');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('erlendr', 'Erlendr is a valiant Nord warrior whose soul now resides in the Hall of Valor after a tragic quest to find Sovngarde ended in him being turned to stone by the wizard Grimkell. His tale serves as both a cautionary legend and inspiration to other Nord warriors, demonstrating both the perils and glory of pursuing one''s destiny regardless of the cost.', 'nord, dragon', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim during the Third Era, Erlendr grew up hearing tales of Sovngarde and developed an obsessive desire to find this legendary realm. He gathered like-minded warriors Hunroor and Nikulas, forming a brotherhood dedicated to discovering the path to the Nordic afterlife. Their quest led them to confront the powerful wizard Grimkell, who cursed them to eternal stone form.', 'Erlendr exemplifies the archetypal Nord warrior - stoic, honor-bound, and unflinchingly dedicated to his goals and companions. Even after his physical form was turned to stone, his spirit remained unbroken, eventually finding its way to Sovngarde as he had always dreamed. He carries himself with the quiet dignity of one who has faced great adversity without surrendering his principles.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with the battle-hardened physique of a seasoned warrior. His features are sharp and angular, typical of Nordic ancestry, with deep-set eyes that reflect years of combat experience. Despite his imposing frame, he moves with the practiced grace of a skilled fighter.', '* Hunroor - Brother-in-arms and fellow questseeker, sharing the same fate * Nikulas - Trusted companion and fellow warrior on the quest for Sovngarde * Grimkell - The wizard who cursed him and his companions to stone form * Tsun - Respected shield-thane of Shor whom he now serves alongside in the Hall of Valor * Shor - The god of the underworld whom he now serves in Sovngarde', 'In life, Erlendr was a questing warrior dedicated to finding Sovngarde. After death, he serves as one of the honored souls in the Hall of Valor, joining other great Nordic heroes in eternal fellowship and combat preparation for Alduin''s final battle.', '* Master-level proficiency in heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Expert swordsman specializing in traditional Nordic fighting styles * Skilled tactician with experience leading warrior bands * Advanced knowledge of Nordic lore and traditions * Exceptional physical strength and endurance typical of Nord warriors', 'Erlendr speaks with a deep, resonant voice that carries the weight of ancient Nordic traditions. His speech is formal and measured, often incorporating references to honor, glory, and the warrior''s way.', '* Defend the Hall of Valor against those who would threaten its sanctity * Guide worthy warriors who seek to enter Sovngarde * Prepare alongside fellow warriors for the final battle of Alduin''s Wall * Maintain the honor and traditions of Nordic warrior culture in the afterlife');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('esbern', 'Esbern is one of the last surviving Blades archivists and a master scholar of dragon lore who went into hiding from the Thalmor after the Great War. His decades of research into the prophecies of Alduin''s return and extensive knowledge of ancient Nordic history make him an invaluable advisor to the Last Dragonborn in their quest to defeat the World-Eater.', 'nord, scholar, skyrimall, dragon', '', '', 'sk_esbern', '', 'Born during the late Third Era, Esbern served as the Master Archivist of Cloud Ruler Temple, the ancient fortress of the Blades. After surviving the Thalmor purge of the Blades during the Great War, he spent decades hiding in Riften''s Ratway while continuing his research into dragon lore and the prophecies of Alduin''s return. His paranoid but prescient warnings about the dragon crisis were largely ignored until events proved him right.', 'Esbern is scholarly, cautious, and deeply paranoid due to years of evading Thalmor hunters, yet remains unfailingly dedicated to his mission of preserving and applying ancient knowledge. Despite his age and eccentricities, he maintains a sharp mind and demonstrates unwavering conviction in matters concerning dragons and prophecy. His academic obsession with dragon lore is matched only by his hatred of the Thalmor and his absolute devotion to the traditions of the Blades.', 'An elderly Nord man with a lined face, graying hair and beard showing his advanced age. Despite years of hiding in poor conditions, he maintains a straight-backed, dignified bearing that hints at his former status. His eyes remain sharp and alert, constantly scanning his surroundings out of ingrained caution.', '* Delphine - Fellow Blade survivor and longtime ally in the fight against both dragons and Thalmor * The Last Dragonborn - Serves as mentor and advisor in the quest to defeat Alduin * Paarthurnax - Views him as an untrustworthy threat that must be eliminated despite his apparent reformation * The Thalmor - Mortal enemies who have hunted him relentlessly since the Great War * Former Blades - Maintains deep reverence for his fallen comrades and their legacy', 'Esbern serves as the primary loremaster and scholar for the reformed Blades, providing crucial historical knowledge and research about dragons. His expertise in translating and interpreting ancient prophecies and dragon lore makes him an irreplaceable resource in understanding the dragon crisis.', '* Master-level knowledge of dragon lore, Nordic history, and ancient prophecies * Accomplished battlemage specializing in Destruction and Conjuration magic * Capable of summoning various atronachs for combat support * Skilled in defensive magic including wards and protective spells * Expert researcher and archivist with extensive knowledge of esoteric texts', 'Esbern speaks with the measured, precise diction of a scholar, often launching into detailed historical explanations and prophectic warnings. His speech frequently includes references to ancient texts and historical events, though paranoia causes him to be initially guarded with strangers.', '* Guide the Last Dragonborn to fulfill their destiny in defeating Alduin * Restore the Blades to their original purpose as dragon hunters * Preserve and apply ancient knowledge about dragons and Nordic history * Eliminate all remaining dragons, including Paarthurnax, whom he views as a threat * Evade capture by the Thalmor while continuing his vital research');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('esmond_tyne', 'Esmond Tyne was a skilled Breton thief and former associate of the Thieves Guild who gained notoriety for stealing valuable crafting secrets, particularly Glover Mallory''s improved bonemold formula. His expertise in infiltration and theft, combined with his ambitious nature, ultimately led to his demise at the hands of rieklings near Castle Karstaag Caverns.', 'breton, thief, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born into modest circumstances in High Rock, Esmond developed his thieving skills on the streets of Wayrest before making his way to Morrowind and eventually Solstheim. His natural talent for acquisition and networking caught the attention of the Thieves Guild, though he preferred operating independently while maintaining loose connections with the organization. His final heist targeting Glover Mallory''s valuable armor formula demonstrated both his ambition and the fatal overconfidence that led to his end.', 'Esmond was characterized by his cunning intelligence and opportunistic nature, always seeking valuable targets that could advance his status and wealth. While capable of charm and persuasion when needed, he harbored an underlying arrogance that made him prone to taking unnecessary risks. His independent streak often put him at odds with more structured criminal organizations, preferring to work alone or with temporary partners.', 'A man of average Breton height with a lean, athletic build suited to his profession of stealth and theft. His features were sharp and angular, typical of his race, with quick, observant eyes that constantly scanned his surroundings. Years of thieves'' work left him with calloused hands and the subtle scars of close escapes.', '* Glover Mallory - Target of his final heist and victim of his formula theft * Thieves Guild - Loose association, though he preferred independent operation * Various Fence Contacts - Network of buyers for stolen goods across Solstheim and Morrowind * Riekling Tribes - Ultimately his killers at Castle Karstaag Caverns', 'Professional thief and occasional Thieves Guild associate who specialized in acquiring valuable documents, formulas, and trade secrets. He maintained a facade of legitimate business dealings while primarily focusing on high-value heists that required careful planning and execution.', '* Expert in stealth, lockpicking, and infiltration techniques * Skilled at identifying valuable documents and trade secrets * Proficient in light armor combat and dagger fighting * Accomplished pickpocket with exceptional sleight of hand * Natural talent for forgery and document authentication', 'Esmond spoke with the refined accent of a High Rock native, often employing clever wordplay and subtle manipulation in his conversations. His tone could shift from charming to businesslike as needed, always maintaining an air of calculated control.', '* Acquire enough wealth and valuable secrets to establish himself as an independent power in the criminal underworld * Build a network of reliable contacts across multiple provinces * Obtain and sell valuable trade secrets and formulas to the highest bidders * Eventually retire wealthy and secure in a position of influence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('estormo', 'Estormo is an ambitious Thalmor agent and skilled mage who serves directly under Ancano during the College of Winterhold crisis. A ruthless operative driven by both duty and personal ambition, he represents the Thalmor''s willingness to eliminate any threats to their dominance over magical artifacts and knowledge.', 'highelf, mage, skyrimall, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born and educated in the Summerset Isles, Estormo rose through the ranks of the Thalmor through a combination of magical aptitude and unwavering loyalty to their cause. His exceptional abilities and ruthless efficiency caught the attention of Ancano, who specifically requested him for the Winterhold operation due to his reputation for getting results regardless of the cost.', 'Estormo embodies the typical Thalmor superiority complex, viewing other races as beneath him and treating them with thinly veiled contempt. He is calculating and ambitious, seeing his mission to stop the player as an opportunity to prove himself worthy of greater responsibility within the Thalmor hierarchy. Despite his arrogance, he is pragmatic and willing to take direct action rather than rely solely on intimidation.', 'Tall and lean like most Altmer, Estormo carries himself with the characteristic grace of his race. His sharp, angular features and cold golden eyes reflect his merciless nature, while his perfectly maintained appearance speaks to his meticulous personality.', '* Ancano - Direct superior and mentor figure within the Thalmor * Thalmor Embassy - Strong connections to the main Thalmor presence in Skyrim * College of Winterhold - Views them as inferior mages and potential threats to Thalmor interests * Other Races - Considers them beneath Altmer dignity and unworthy of magical knowledge', 'Estormo serves as a specialized Thalmor agent, focusing on magical artifacts and potential threats to Thalmor supremacy. His position requires him to act as both a spy and enforcer, eliminating obstacles to Thalmor goals while gathering intelligence about powerful magical artifacts.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Highly trained in magical combat and ward spells * Proficient in stealth and tracking * Advanced knowledge of enchanting and magical artifacts * Skilled in interrogation and intimidation techniques', 'Speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary typical of educated Altmer, frequently employing condescending tones and subtle threats. His speech patterns reflect both his superior education and his belief in Thalmor supremacy.', '* Advance within the Thalmor hierarchy through successful missions and proven loyalty * Secure powerful magical artifacts for the Thalmor''s use * Eliminate threats to Thalmor magical supremacy * Prove himself worthy of greater authority within the organization');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('etienne_rarnis', 'Etienne Rarnis is a skilled Breton thief and member of the Thieves Guild who endured brutal interrogation at the hands of the Thalmor while protecting information about Esbern. Despite his roguish exterior and cocky attitude, he demonstrates remarkable loyalty and resilience, refusing to fully betray his Guild''s secrets even under extreme duress.', 'breton, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Etienne made his way to Skyrim seeking opportunity in the criminal underworld. He eventually found his place within the Thieves Guild in Riften, where his natural talents for stealth and subterfuge made him a valuable member. His capture by the Thalmor while gathering intelligence about their activities proved to be a pivotal moment in his life, testing both his resolve and loyalty.', 'Etienne maintains a cocky and cheeky demeanor that masks deeper layers of resilience and loyalty. Despite his roguish nature, he demonstrates tremendous strength of character through his resistance to Thalmor torture, revealing only the minimum information necessary to survive. His experiences have left him with a deep-seated hatred for the Thalmor, though he copes with trauma through humor and bravado.', 'A typical Breton of average height and lean build, suited to stealth and agility. His face bears subtle scars from his Thalmor interrogation, and his body shows signs of the torture he endured. His movements remain graceful and precise despite his ordeal.', '* Thieves Guild - Loyal member and brother-in-arms * Thalmor - Bitter enemies who tortured him for information * Esbern - Knew of his existence but protected his identity under torture * Mercer Frey - Guild Master he serves under, though with some reservation * Brynjolf - Respects as a senior Guild member and possible mentor', 'As a member of the Thieves Guild, Etienne specializes in gathering intelligence and performing covert operations. His role often involves reconnaissance and information gathering, though his capture by the Thalmor has temporarily reduced his active field operations while he recovers in the Ragged Flagon.', '* Expert in stealth and infiltration techniques * Skilled lockpicker and pickpocket * Proficient in gathering intelligence and reconnaissance * Capable swordsman with preference for light blades * Strong mental fortitude and resistance to interrogation', 'Speaks with a slight Breton accent and employs witty, sometimes sarcastic remarks. His casual, confident tone often disguises careful word choice, particularly when discussing sensitive information.', '* Recover fully from his Thalmor imprisonment and return to active Guild duties * Seek revenge against the Thalmor for his torture and imprisonment * Contribute to the Guild''s return to prominence in Skyrim * Maintain his position and reputation within the Thieves Guild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('evette_san', 'Evette San is a determined Nord merchant who runs a beverage stand in Solitude, specializing in her father''s spiced wine recipe. Despite financial struggles and uncertain times, she maintains her family''s legacy through her business while dealing with both the political tensions in Skyrim and her complicated relationship with her alcoholic father.', 'nord, merchant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Evette learned the spiced wine recipe from her father Octieve San, a notorious town drunk who managed to create something worthwhile despite his flaws. She established her beverage stand to make an honest living and preserve the one positive contribution from her father''s legacy, building her reputation through the popular Burning of King Olaf festival.', 'Hardworking and resilient, Evette maintains a positive attitude despite financial hardships and family troubles. She shows determination in overcoming business obstacles while displaying empathy for others, though she carries underlying anxiety about her economic situation and her father''s influence on her reputation.', 'A Nord woman of average height with the sturdy build typical of her race. Her features show signs of long hours working outdoors at her market stall, with weathered skin from constant exposure to Solitude''s harsh climate.', '* Octieve San - Her father, a known alcoholic whose reputation affects her standing in the community * East Empire Company - Tense business relationship due to shipping delays * Bards College - Valuable business connection through festival participation * Vittoria Vici - Important contact for securing spice shipments * Local Guards - Regular customers who help maintain order around her stall', 'Evette operates a beverage stand in Solitude''s market district, specializing in spiced wine and other drinks. She manages all aspects of her small business, from securing ingredients to marketing and sales, while maintaining her family''s traditional recipes.', '* Expert knowledge of wine brewing and spicing techniques * Skilled at merchant trading and haggling * Proficient at managing inventory and supply chains * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger', 'Speaks with a friendly, market-vendor''s charm while maintaining a professional Nord accent. Her sales pitch is warm and inviting, often emphasizing the traditional and homey aspects of her products.', '* Maintain and grow her spiced wine business despite political upheaval * Secure reliable supply chains for her specialty ingredients * Preserve her father''s recipe while establishing her own positive reputation * Expand her customer base beyond festival attendance');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('evul_seloth', 'Evul Seloth is a resilient Dark Elf miner who exemplifies the hardy spirit of Raven Rock''s working class during its economic recovery. After enduring unemployment when the mine closed, he has returned to his life''s work with renewed appreciation and determination, serving as an example of Solstheim''s perseverance.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Raven Rock, Evul comes from a long line of miners who worked the ebony veins of Solstheim. He weathered the mine''s closure and subsequent economic hardship, refusing to leave the island despite many others abandoning the settlement. His dedication to his homeland and profession was rewarded when the mine reopened, allowing him to restore his family''s traditional way of life.', 'Evul is an optimistic and hardworking individual who takes genuine pride in his mining profession. He maintains a positive attitude even during difficult work conditions, often encouraging his fellow miners with his enthusiasm. Despite the harsh realities of mining life, he remains grateful for the opportunity to work and views his job as a crucial part of Raven Rock''s identity and survival.', 'Evul has the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his Dunmer heritage, with his face bearing the weathered look common to career miners. His muscular build and calloused hands reflect years of physical labor in the mines, while his posture remains strong despite the demanding nature of his work.', '* Fellow Miners - Maintains positive working relationships and camaraderie * Family - Has a wife and children he supports through his mining work * Crescius Caerellius - Respects the mine''s supervisor and is grateful for the reopening * East Empire Company - Views them with cautious optimism after the mine''s reopening', 'Evul works as an ebony miner in Raven Rock Mine, performing the physically demanding task of extracting valuable ebony ore from the deep veins within the mine. His position is crucial to both Raven Rock''s economy and his family''s livelihood, representing the backbone of the settlement''s working class.', '* Experienced in ebony mining techniques and ore identification * Proficient with mining tools and equipment * Knowledge of mine safety practices and procedures * Physical endurance and strength from years of mining work * Basic understanding of ebony ore quality assessment', 'Evul speaks in the distinct accent of Morrowind natives, using informal and straightforward language. His speech often includes mining terminology and expressions of gratitude for his work, frequently punctuated by enthusiastic remarks about the mine''s prosperity.', '* Maintain steady work to provide for his family and ensure their security * Help restore Raven Rock Mine to its former glory and productivity * Pass down his mining knowledge and skills to the next generation * Contribute to Raven Rock''s economic recovery and stability');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('eydis', 'Eydis is a resilient Nord innkeeper who maintains the historic Old Hroldan Inn, a site of significant historical importance tied to Tiber Septim''s legacy. She manages the establishment with quiet determination while harboring personal secrets, particularly regarding her missing husband''s fate, which she conceals from her young son.', 'nord, innkeeper, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Originally from the Reach, Eydis took over the operation of Old Hroldan Inn at some point before the Civil War, recognizing the historical significance of the location. Her husband''s disappearance (whether due to death, abandonment, or other circumstances) led her to create a protective fiction about his whereabouts, telling her son that his father is away fighting in the war to shield him from a potentially darker truth.', 'Eydis is a hardworking and dedicated innkeeper who never takes breaks, suggesting both strong work ethic and possible anxiety about maintaining the establishment''s success. She shows maternal protectiveness through her willingness to deceive her son about his father''s fate, while also displaying pride in her son''s capabilities and the inn''s historical significance.', 'As a Nord woman, Eydis likely possesses the typical hardy Nordic features including fair skin and a strong physical build suited to the harsh climate of Skyrim. She shows signs of aging and wear from years of continuous work, though she maintains an appearance appropriate for a professional innkeeper.', '* Skuli - Her young son whom she protectively shields from the truth about his father * Leontius Salvius - Employee who assists in running the inn * Missing Husband - Absent spouse whose true fate remains unknown * Inn Patrons - Professional relationships maintained through her role as publican', 'Eydis serves as the owner and publican of the Old Hroldan Inn, a historic establishment famous for once hosting Tiber Septim. She manages all aspects of the inn''s operation, from serving customers to maintaining the property, with particular pride in preserving its historical significance.', '* Experienced innkeeper with strong business management abilities * Proficient in food preparation and beverage service * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Knowledge of local history, particularly regarding Tiber Septim''s campaign', 'She speaks with the direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord innkeepers, while maintaining a sense of pride when discussing the inn''s historical significance. Her tone becomes notably guarded and careful when addressing questions about her husband.', '* Maintain the historic Old Hroldan Inn as a successful business and preserve its historical significance * Protect her son Skuli from the truth about his father while ensuring his well-being * Keep the inn''s reputation as Tiber Septim''s resting place intact and profitable');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('faendal', 'Faendal is a skilled Bosmer archer and hunter who settled in the Nordic village of Riverwood, where he works as both a lumber mill worker and the town''s primary provider of game meat. Despite embracing his new life in Skyrim, he maintains his Wood Elven cultural identity while pursuing a romantic interest in Camilla Valerius, putting him at odds with his rival Sven.', 'woodelf, archer, whiterun, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, Faendal migrated to Skyrim seeking new opportunities, eventually settling in the small village of Riverwood. His natural Bosmer affinity for archery and hunting helped him quickly establish himself as a valuable member of the community, though he often feels the cultural disconnect of being one of the few mer in a predominantly Nordic settlement.', 'Faendal is hardworking and reliable, though he harbors a passionate and sometimes jealous nature when it comes to his feelings for Camilla Valerius. While generally honest, he''s willing to engage in deception to win Camilla''s affections, revealing a more complex moral character. He takes pride in his archery skills and hunting abilities, occasionally displaying a boastful streak.', 'As a Bosmer, Faendal has the characteristic slight build and pointed ears of his race, standing shorter than the local Nords. His face shows the angular features typical of mer, with sharp cheekbones and almond-shaped eyes. His body is lean and athletic from years of hunting and physical labor.', '* Camilla Valerius - Object of his romantic affections, though their relationship remains uncertain * Sven - Rival for Camilla''s affections and fellow Riverwood resident * Gerdur - Employer at the Riverwood lumber mill * Lucan Valerius - Camilla''s brother and local shopkeeper * Local Riverwood residents - Generally amicable professional relationships', 'Faendal splits his time between working at the Riverwood lumber mill and serving as the village''s primary hunter. He also acts as an archery trainer, offering his expertise to those willing to learn. His hunting provides essential meat and pelts to the local community.', '* Expert archer with exceptional accuracy and teaching ability * Skilled hunter and tracker in various weather conditions * Proficient in wilderness survival and game dressing * Experienced woodcutter and lumber mill worker * Basic proficiency with daggers for close-quarter defense', 'Faendal speaks with the measured tone of someone who has adapted to Nordic culture while maintaining his Bosmeri identity. His speech often reveals both his pride in his abilities and his slight outsider status, frequently making comparative observations about Nord culture versus his own.', '* Win Camilla Valerius''s affections and establish a romantic relationship with her * Maintain his position as Riverwood''s premier hunter and archer * Find a balance between his Bosmeri heritage and his adopted Nordic home * Potentially advance his standing in the community beyond his current roles');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('faida', 'Faida is a hardworking Nord innkeeper who runs the Four Shields Tavern in Dragon Bridge with dedication and pride. She maintains a romantic relationship with Imperial Commander Gaius Maro while mentoring young Julienne Lylvieve in the innkeeping trade, representing a bridge between Imperial and Nord cultures in this strategic settlement.', 'nord, innkeeper, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Originally a barmaid at the Winking Skeever in Solitude, Faida married and eventually took over ownership of the Four Shields Tavern after her husband''s death. She has maintained the establishment as a respectable inn that serves both locals and travelers, particularly Imperial soldiers passing through Dragon Bridge.', 'Faida is a practical and industrious Nord woman who takes pride in her work while maintaining high standards for her establishment. She shows a nurturing side through her mentorship of Julienne Lylvieve, while her relationship with Gaius Maro reveals her capacity for deep emotional attachment despite the political tensions between Nords and Imperials.', 'A mature Nord woman with the sturdy build typical of her race, showing the physical resilience needed for the demanding work of running an inn. Her features likely bear the weathered but dignified look common to Nord women who have spent years in service-oriented work.', '* Gaius Maro - Romantic partner and Imperial Commander whom she deeply cares for * Julienne Lylvieve - Apprentice whom she mentors in the innkeeping trade * Late Husband - Former owner of the Four Shields Tavern, fondly remembered * Dragon Bridge Residents - Maintains good relations with locals, particularly the Lylvieve family * Imperial Soldiers - Regular customers due to Dragon Bridge''s strategic location', 'Faida serves as the proprietor of the Four Shields Tavern, managing all aspects of the establishment from serving food and drink to maintaining the premises and handling business affairs. She takes her role as a mentor seriously, teaching Julienne the intricacies of running an inn while maintaining the establishment''s reputation as a reliable stopping point for travelers.', '* Experienced in tavern management and customer service * Knowledgeable about food preparation and storage * Capable of basic self-defense with an iron dagger * Skilled at managing books and maintaining a profitable business * Diplomatic abilities in handling both Imperial soldiers and local Nord customers', 'Faida speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord innkeepers, but maintains a professional tone suitable for her establishment''s diverse clientele. Her speech reveals both her practical nature and her pride in her work, while showing warmth when interacting with regular customers.', '* Maintain the Four Shields Tavern as a successful and reputable establishment * Successfully train Julienne Lylvieve to become a capable innkeeper * Sustain her relationship with Gaius Maro despite the political tensions * Preserve her late husband''s legacy through the continued success of the inn');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('falas_selvayn', 'Falas Selvayn is a shrewd Dark Elf merchant operating a mysterious night-time trading post in Skyrim, dealing in goods of questionable origin. His late-night business hours and evasive nature suggest connections to Skyrim''s criminal underground, though he maintains a veneer of legitimate commerce through his established trading post.', 'darkelf, merchant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Falas fled west following the Red Mountain''s eruption, eventually establishing himself in Skyrim''s grey market economy. Through careful networking and strategic positioning, he built his current operation at the Ramshackle Trading Post, choosing its remote location and unusual hours to avoid unwanted scrutiny from guards and legitimate merchants.', 'Falas is deliberately curt and guarded, maintaining professional distance from his customers while revealing little about himself or his business practices. His suspicious nature and careful vetting of customers suggests experience with dangerous transactions, while his practical approach to commerce indicates a pragmatic survivor rather than a hardened criminal.', 'A lean, weather-worn Dunmer with sharp, angular features typical of his race and keen red eyes that miss little. His frame is wiry but strong from years of moving cargo, with calloused hands that speak to regular physical labor despite his merchant profession.', '* Thieves Guild - Likely maintains unofficial connections as a fence, though keeps association discrete * Local Bandits - Possible suppliers of ''found'' merchandise, relationship strictly business * Guard Patrols - Maintains careful distance while ensuring minimal interference through strategic timing * Regular Customers - Small network of trusted clients who know his operating hours', 'Falas operates as a semi-legitimate trader, running his business during unconventional hours that suit his particular clientele. His role likely extends beyond simple merchant to include dealing in questionably obtained goods, though he maintains enough legitimate trade to avoid official scrutiny.', '* Expert in valuation of goods and haggling * Skilled at identifying valuable merchandise quickly * Proficient in security and surveillance techniques * Basic combat abilities for self-defense * Experienced in discrete goods transportation and storage', 'Speaks in clipped, efficient sentences with a slight Morrowind accent, often using intentionally vague terminology when discussing business matters. His vocabulary is practical and direct, avoiding flowery language or unnecessary elaboration.', '* Establish a more secure and profitable trading network while maintaining anonymity * Eventually expand operations to multiple locations across Skyrim * Accumulate enough wealth to retire comfortably, possibly returning to Morrowind * Avoid any serious entanglements with law enforcement or criminal organizations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('faldrus', 'Faldrus is a devout Dark Elf mage on a sacred pilgrimage to the Shrine of Azura, driven by deep spiritual conviction and mystical pursuit. His focused determination and expertise in elemental magic mark him as a serious practitioner of both magical and religious disciplines, though he maintains a reserved demeanor in his interactions with others.', 'darkelf, mage, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Faldrus likely fled to Skyrim following the Red Mountain''s eruption, like many other Dunmer refugees. His devotion to Azura, one of the ''good'' Daedric Princes still widely worshipped by the Dark Elves, suggests a traditional upbringing in Dunmeri culture and religious practices. His magical training and solitary lifestyle indicate possible education at the College of Winterhold or through private tutelage.', 'Faldrus exhibits a focused and solitary nature, preferring spiritual contemplation to social interaction. His brief but polite responses to others reveal a character who values purpose over pleasantries, maintaining a respectful but distant demeanor. His unwavering dedication to his pilgrimage demonstrates both religious devotion and strong self-discipline.', 'As a male Dunmer, Faldrus possesses the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race. His face follows the typical angular features of male Dark Elves, though he distinguishes himself with a unique hairstyle. His body likely shows the lean build common to dedicated mages who prioritize mental discipline over physical strength.', '* Aranea Ienith - Fellow worshipper of Azura whom he joins at the shrine * Azura - Daedric Prince he devoutly worships and seeks to honor through pilgrimage * College of Winterhold - Possible former association as a student or researcher * Local Nords - Likely maintains cautious distance due to their general distrust of both Dunmer and magic users', 'Faldrus serves as an independent mage-pilgrim, dedicating his time to spiritual pursuits and the worship of Azura. His lifestyle suggests he may support himself through magical services or research when not engaged in religious devotions, though his primary focus remains his spiritual journey.', '* Accomplished practitioner of elemental magic * Experienced wilderness survivor capable of long-distance travel * Knowledgeable in Daedric lore and religious customs * Proficient in navigation and pathfinding across Skyrim''s harsh terrain', 'Faldrus speaks in a formal, concise manner typical of educated Dunmer, using precise language while maintaining religious reverence. His responses are invariably polite but brief, reflecting his focus on his spiritual mission rather than casual conversation.', '* Complete his pilgrimage to the Shrine of Azura * Deepen his spiritual connection with the Daedric Prince of Twilight * Join the permanent worship community at Azura''s Shrine * Seek greater understanding of Azura''s prophecies and wisdom');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('faleen', 'Faleen is a fierce and dedicated Redguard warrior serving as housecarl to Jarl Igmund of Markarth. She embodies the proud warrior tradition of her people while maintaining unwavering loyalty to her jarl, serving as both his primary protector and trusted advisor in matters of security.', 'redguard, noble, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born and raised in the warrior tradition of the Redguards, Faleen likely came to Skyrim seeking opportunities to prove her martial prowess. Her exceptional combat skills and steadfast dedication eventually earned her the prestigious position of housecarl to Jarl Igmund, a role she has maintained through both peaceful times and political turmoil.', 'Faleen is stern, vigilant, and deeply committed to her duties as housecarl. She maintains a professional demeanor but harbors a softer side, as evidenced by her hidden romantic potential with Calcelmo. Her fierce hatred of the Forsworn stems from their murder of Igmund''s father, driving her to be especially protective of her jarl.', 'Faleen possesses the athletic build and dark complexion characteristic of Redguards, with a warrior''s physique honed through years of combat training. Her bearing is proud and militant, reflecting her role as a professional protector and her Redguard heritage.', '* Jarl Igmund - Sworn lord whom she serves with unwavering loyalty * Calcelmo - Court wizard who harbors secret romantic feelings for her * Raerek - Fellow member of Igmund''s court with whom she collaborates on security matters * The Forsworn - Bitter enemies whom she despises for killing Igmund''s father', 'As housecarl to Jarl Igmund, Faleen serves as his personal bodyguard and security advisor, responsible for protecting both his person and the Mournful Throne. She maintains vigilant watch over Understone Keep and coordinates with other guards to ensure the jarl''s safety.', '* Expert in traditional Redguard combat techniques with proficiency in both one-handed weapons and shields * Trained in bodyguard tactics and threat assessment * Skilled archer capable of both close and long-range combat * Strategic expertise in security operations and guard coordination', 'Faleen speaks with the direct, no-nonsense tone of a professional warrior, though her Redguard accent occasionally surfaces. Her speech is formal when addressing visitors to the keep but becomes more aggressive when dealing with perceived threats.', '* Ensure the continued safety and security of Jarl Igmund * Maintain order in Markarth and protect against Forsworn threats * Avenge Igmund''s father by eliminating the Forsworn presence in the Reach * Navigate her unexpected romantic connection with Calcelmo while maintaining professional duties');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('falion', 'Falion is a mysterious and highly skilled Redguard conjurer who serves as Morthal''s resident wizard despite the townspeople''s distrust. He is a master of conjuration magic with extensive knowledge of vampirism, planes of Oblivion, and various magical disciplines, while also serving as a guardian and mentor to his young apprentice Agni.', 'redguard, mage, hjaalmarch, vampire', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally a teacher at the College of Winterhold, Falion left due to his intense dislike of the institution. His extensive magical research has led him to traverse the planes of Oblivion, encounter Daedra and even Dwemer, and study life-extending magics alongside vampires. He ultimately settled in Morthal to continue his research and protect the town, while also taking in the orphaned Agni as his apprentice.', 'Falion is reclusive and mysterious, preferring solitude for his research over social interaction. Despite his intimidating reputation, he shows a compassionate side through his care for Agni and his willingness to help cure vampirism. He is proud of his magical knowledge but maintains strong ethical boundaries, having rejected vampirism to protect his apprentice.', 'A middle-aged Redguard man with dark skin and sharp, scrutinizing eyes that reflect his magical knowledge and wisdom. His face bears the weathered look of someone who has spent countless hours in study and magical practice. His body is lean and maintains the natural athleticism common to his race.', '* Agni - His apprentice and ward whom he protects and teaches magic * Jonna - His sister who runs the Moorside Inn, though their relationship is kept quiet * Jarl Idgrod - Supports his presence in Morthal despite public mistrust * Morthal Residents - Generally distrustful of him and his magical practices * College of Winterhold - Former employer whom he now despises', 'Falion serves as Morthal''s resident wizard, selling magical items and spells from his home. He is a master-level trainer in Conjuration and provides the unique service of curing vampirism. His work includes both magical research and protecting the town, though much of his activity remains secretive.', '* Master-level expertise in Conjuration magic * Extensive knowledge of vampirism and its cure * Experienced in traversing Oblivion planes and communicating with Daedra * Proficient in enchanting and alchemy * Advanced understanding of life-extending magics and undead lore', 'Falion speaks with the measured tone of a scholar, often using technical magical terminology and maintaining a formal, somewhat aloof manner. His words carry authority and wisdom, though they can sometimes be tinged with irritation when dealing with suspicious townspeople.', '* Continue his magical research and experiments in relative peace * Protect and train Agni to become a skilled mage * Keep Morthal safe from magical threats while maintaining his privacy * Further his understanding of life-extending magic and planar travel * Maintain his ethical standards while advancing magical knowledge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('falk_firebeard', 'Falk Firebeard is the capable and diplomatic steward of Jarl Elisif the Fair, effectively running Solitude''s day-to-day operations in the wake of High King Torygg''s death. As the practical administrator of Skyrim''s capital city, he carefully balances political tensions while managing both local affairs and the broader implications of the civil war.', 'nord, noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Falk worked his way up through the ranks of civil service, eventually earning the trust of High King Torygg who appointed him as steward. Following Torygg''s death at Ulfric''s hands, Falk became the primary advisor and administrator for the widowed Jarl Elisif, effectively running the hold while she mourns and learns to rule.', 'Pragmatic, diplomatic, and fiercely loyal to both Solitude and the Empire, Falk approaches his duties with careful consideration and political acumen. He shows remarkable patience in managing Elisif''s sometimes naive suggestions while maintaining respect for her authority, and demonstrates a protective nature toward both the city and its ruler.', 'A sturdy Nord man in his late forties with distinctive red-tinted beard and hair that earned him his surname. His bearing is dignified and formal, with the weathered features typical of a Nord but maintained with the grooming expected of a court official.', '* Jarl Elisif the Fair - His direct superior whom he loyally serves while subtly guiding her development as a ruler * General Tullius - Professional ally in maintaining Imperial control and city security * Bryling - Rumored romantic interest, though both maintain professional discretion * Thane Erikur - Rival court member whose influence he works to check * Sybille Stentor - Court Wizard colleague with whom he maintains a cautious working relationship', 'As steward of Solitude, Falk manages the city''s administration, finances, and diplomatic affairs while serving as chief advisor to Jarl Elisif. He oversees everything from property sales to military coordination with the Imperial Legion, effectively acting as the practical ruler of Haafingar in all but name.', '* Expert in administrative management and bureaucratic operations * Skilled diplomat and negotiator * Competent warrior with traditional Nord military training * Deeply knowledgeable about Solitude''s history and politics * Proficient at managing court intrigues and political relationships', 'Falk speaks with formal, measured tones befitting his position, employing diplomatic language that carefully weighs each word. His manner is direct but respectful, showing deference to authority while maintaining the dignity of his office.', '* Guide Jarl Elisif into becoming a capable ruler worthy of the High Queen title * Maintain Solitude''s stability and prosperity during the civil war * Preserve Imperial control over Skyrim while protecting local Nordic traditions * Secure Haafingar''s defenses against both Stormcloak aggression and supernatural threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('falmer_servant', 'A corrupted Dunmer who has pledged his allegiance to the twisted Falmer dwelling in Blackreach''s depths. Once a normal Dark Elf, he now serves as a human guardian and servant to these blind, subterranean creatures, defending their territory with fanatical devotion.', 'darkelf, peasant', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally a Dunmer explorer or researcher who ventured too deep into Dwemer ruins, he was captured by the Falmer but somehow earned their trust rather than becoming their slave or meal. Years of living in darkness and exposure to Falmer society has warped his mind, leading him to embrace their savage culture and reject his former life above ground.', 'Aggressive and territorial, showing unwavering loyalty to his Falmer masters while maintaining enough sanity to warn away intruders when alone. His mind has been twisted by isolation and darkness, resulting in paranoid and hostile behavior towards all surface dwellers. Despite his madness, he retains enough intelligence to serve as an effective guardian and communicate in coherent speech.', 'A gaunt, pale-skinned Dunmer with the characteristic red eyes of his race, though years in darkness have left them developed an unnatural, luminescent quality. His body shows signs of adaptation to underground living, with a slightly hunched posture and unusually pale skin for a Dark Elf.', '* Falmer - Serves them with absolute loyalty and devotion * Surface Dwellers - Views them as threats and potential enemies * Blackreach Denizens - Peaceful coexistence with other Falmer-allied creatures * Former Life Connections - All abandoned or forgotten', 'Acts as a guardian and servant for the Falmer, protecting their territory from intruders and likely helping maintain their underground dwellings. May assist in hunting, gathering fungi, or tending chaurus breeding grounds.', '* Adapted to navigating dark underground environments with exceptional skill * Capable fighter with whatever weapons the Falmer provide * Understanding of Falmer behavior patterns and social structure * Knowledge of Blackreach''s layout and defensive positions', 'Speaks in harsh, threatening tones with an aggressive edge, often issuing warnings and threats to intruders. His vocabulary remains coherent but reflects his twisted loyalties and territorial nature.', '* Protect Falmer territory from all surface dwellers and intruders * Maintain his position of trust among the Falmer * Drive away or eliminate any threats to his Falmer masters * Preserve the isolated existence of his underground society');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fanari_strong-voice', 'Fanari Strong-Voice is the respected chief of the Skaal Village, chosen by her people to lead them after the passing of Skaf the Giant. She embodies the traditional values of the Skaal, serving as both a spiritual and practical leader who maintains their ancient Nordic traditions while protecting them from modern threats.', 'nord, peasant, solstheim, skall', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised among the Skaal, Fanari demonstrated leadership qualities from an early age, earning respect through her wisdom and strong conviction in their traditional ways. She was mentored by previous chief Skaf the Giant in the ways of leadership and the ancient traditions of their people, eventually being chosen by the village to succeed him upon his death.', 'Fanari is defined by her directness and unwavering commitment to her people''s wellbeing, never hesitating to voice her opinions when she believes something is right or wrong. She possesses a practical wisdom that balances respect for ancient Skaal traditions with the pragmatic needs of village leadership. Though she can be stern with outsiders who show little compassion, she demonstrates genuine warmth and gratitude toward those who aid her community, viewing their kindness as precious as sunlight on a cold day.
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('faralda', 'Faralda is a highly accomplished High Elf sorceress who serves as both gatekeeper and senior instructor at the College of Winterhold, specializing in Destruction magic. She embodies the measured confidence and ambition typical of Altmer mages, maintaining high standards for prospective students while nurturing genuine magical talent.', 'highelf, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born and raised in the Summerset Isles, Faralda demonstrated exceptional magical aptitude from an early age and pursued advanced studies in Destruction magic. After achieving mastery of her craft, she relocated to Skyrim to join the College of Winterhold, where her talents and dedication earned her a position as a senior faculty member.', 'Faralda exhibits the characteristic pride and ambition of her Altmer heritage, though tempered by genuine dedication to magical scholarship and teaching. She maintains high professional standards and can be stern with prospective students, but shows genuine support for those who demonstrate real magical potential. Her rivalry with Nirya over both professional advancement and romantic interests reveals a more personal side beneath her composed exterior.', 'Faralda possesses the typical tall, slender build and golden skin tone of the Altmer race, with sharp, angular facial features and the characteristic pointed ears of mer. Her bearing is graceful and dignified, reflecting years of magical practice and academic position.', '* Sergius Turrianus - Secret romantic interest, though complicated by similar attention from Nirya * Nirya - Professional rival and competitor for both advancement and Sergius''s affections * Ancano - Distrusted colleague whom she suspects of being a Thalmor spy * Mirabelle Ervine - Respected superior and fellow senior faculty member * Students - Maintains professional but supportive relationships with those who prove worthy', 'Faralda serves as both the College''s gatekeeper, testing new applicants, and as a senior instructor specializing in Destruction magic. She maintains regular teaching duties while also conducting research and providing advanced magical training to qualified students.', '* Master-level expertise in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Proficient in defensive magic including wards and protective spells * Skilled instructor with deep theoretical knowledge of magical principles * Accomplished researcher in advanced magical studies * Competent administrator with experience in academic oversight', 'Faralda speaks with the formal, educated diction typical of senior academic staff, often using precise magical terminology and maintaining a professional tone. Her manner of speech reflects both her Altmer heritage and her position as a respected instructor, though she can be more direct when expressing ambition or rivalry.', '* Advance to the position of Master Wizard or potentially even Arch-Mage * Further develop and document advanced applications of Destruction magic * Maintain the College''s standards while identifying and nurturing genuine magical talent * Establish herself as the preeminent authority on Destruction magic in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('farengar_secret-fire', 'Farengar Secret-Fire is a dedicated scholar and court wizard who combines Nordic pragmatism with an intense passion for magical research, particularly focusing on dragons. His position in Dragonsreach places him at the intersection of practical court politics and arcane studies, making him one of the few respected mages in a culture traditionally skeptical of magic.', 'nord, mage, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born to a Nord family that likely had previous magical practitioners, Farengar pursued magical studies despite the typical Nordic distrust of mages. He likely received formal training at the College of Winterhold before being appointed as court wizard to Jarl Balgruuf, a position he has held for several years while building his reputation as a reliable magical advisor and scholar.', 'Farengar exhibits a somewhat condescending and aloof demeanor, often speaking down to those he considers intellectually inferior. He shows intense enthusiasm for magical research and dragon lore, sometimes to the point of social awkwardness. Despite his arrogant exterior, he maintains a strong sense of duty to his position and the safety of Whiterun.', 'A middle-aged Nord with sharp, angular features typical of his race, though somewhat softened by an indoor scholarly lifestyle. His physique is less muscular than the typical Nord warrior, reflecting his dedication to magical pursuits rather than martial training. His hands show the subtle scarring common to those who regularly work with magical energies.', '* Jarl Balgruuf the Greater - His patron and direct superior whom he serves as magical advisor * Delphine - Mysterious collaborator in dragon research * Proventus Avenicci - Fellow advisor to the Jarl, maintaining a professional but sometimes tense relationship * Arcadia - Professional relationship with the local alchemist, occasionally trading supplies * College of Winterhold - Maintains loose connections with his presumed alma mater', 'As Court Wizard of Whiterun, Farengar serves as the Jarl''s primary advisor on magical and supernatural matters. He maintains a magical laboratory in Dragonsreach where he conducts research, sells spells, and provides enchanting services to those deemed worthy.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly focusing on fire-based spells * Accomplished enchanter with deep knowledge of magical artifacts * Scholarly expertise in dragon lore and ancient Nordic history * Competent alchemist with knowledge of magical reagents * Basic combat training with daggers as backup to magical abilities', 'He speaks with a condescending, scholarly tone, often using complex terminology and showing impatience with those who don''t match his intellectual level. His speech patterns reflect his academic background, frequently peppering conversations with magical terminology and theoretical concepts.', '* Advance understanding of dragon lore and document their return to Skyrim * Expand his magical knowledge and research capabilities * Maintain his position of respect within Whiterun despite general Nordic distrust of magic * Acquire rare magical artifacts and ancient knowledge for study');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('farkas', 'Farkas is a formidable Nord warrior and member of the Companions'' inner circle, known for his straightforward nature and physical prowess despite being considered intellectually simple by some. As a werewolf and master trainer in Heavy Armor, he serves as both a mentor and Shield-Brother to new Companions, embodying the organization''s values of honor and martial excellence.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, companions, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Raised alongside his twin brother Vilkas in Jorrvaskr from a very young age after their father Jergen brought them to the Companions. Though their father never returned from war, the twins found a new family among the Companions, eventually rising to become members of the Circle and accepting the gift of lycanthropy.', 'Despite being often dismissed as dim-witted, Farkas possesses a straightforward, honest nature and unwavering loyalty to his Shield-Siblings. He approaches problems directly and values action over words, showing a particular distaste for political complexities. Though capable of great ferocity in battle, he maintains a gentle demeanor in peaceful situations and shows reluctance to use his werewolf abilities.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with the robust build typical of a seasoned warrior. His face bears the weathered features common to Nords, with distinctive war paint and long dark hair. Like his twin Vilkas, he has strong Nordic features, though his expression tends to be more open and less stern.', '* Vilkas - Twin brother and fellow Circle member, sharing a close bond * Kodlak Whitemane - Respected mentor and father figure who helped raise him * Aela the Huntress - Fellow Circle member and Shield-Sister * Skjor - Former Shield-Brother and Circle member * Jergen - Biological father who brought them to the Companions but never returned', 'As a member of the Companions'' inner circle, Farkas serves as a warrior, trainer, and Shield-Brother to fellow members. He specializes in training others in Heavy Armor techniques and leads newer members on various assignments, from simple bounty hunting to more complex missions.', '* Master-level expertise in Heavy Armor combat techniques * Exceptional strength and proficiency with two-handed weapons * Werewolf transformation abilities, though rarely used * Advanced combat tactics and battlefield awareness * Natural leadership abilities in combat situations', 'Speaks in simple, direct terms with a thick Nordic accent, often understating his own intelligence with self-deprecating remarks. Tends to be brief and to-the-point in his communication, avoiding complex explanations or flowery language.', '* Uphold the honor and traditions of the Companions * Protect and mentor new members of the Companions * Come to terms with his lycanthropy and find peace with his dual nature * Support his brother Vilkas and maintain the strength of the Circle');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('faryl_atheron', 'Faryl Atheron is a pragmatic Dark Elf farmhand who has carved out a modest but stable life working for Nords in Windhelm, despite the city''s racial tensions. Unlike many of his fellow Dunmer, he takes a practical approach to survival, choosing steady employment over pride while maintaining a delicate balance between his cultural identity and the necessity of integration.', 'darkelf, peasant, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born into the Atheron family, Faryl grew up in Windhelm''s Gray Quarter alongside his siblings Aval and Suvaris. Unlike his ancestors who likely fled from Morrowind during the Red Mountain eruption, Faryl has never seen his ancestral homeland, having spent his entire life adapting to Skyrim''s harsh climate and even harsher social conditions.', 'Faryl exhibits a practical and levelheaded nature, accepting the realities of his situation without the bitterness that characterizes many of his fellow Dunmer. He values financial stability over racial pride, showing patience with his demanding Nord employer while maintaining a quiet dignity. Despite facing discrimination, he maintains a diplomatic approach, though his conversations reveal a dry wit and subtle sarcasm.', 'Like most Dunmer, Faryl has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race. His body shows the physical conditioning of someone accustomed to manual labor, with callused hands and a sturdy frame built through years of farm work. Weather-beaten features reflect his long hours working outdoors in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Aval Atheron - Brother who disapproves of his work for Nords * Suvaris Atheron - Sister who, like him, works for Nords * Bolfrida Brandy-Mug - Nord employer with whom he maintains a professional if sometimes strained relationship * Rolff Stone-Fist - Antagonistic citizen whose racist rants he must regularly endure * Gray Quarter Community - Fellow Dunmer with whom he maintains connections despite his integration with Nord society', 'Faryl works as a farmhand at Brandy-Mug Farm, managing crops in Skyrim''s challenging climate. His position requires expertise in agricultural techniques and adaptation to the harsh growing conditions of the region, while also demanding social navigation skills to maintain his position as a Dunmer working for a Nord employer.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of crop management in harsh climates * Physical endurance and strength from manual labor * Diplomatic interpersonal skills for navigating racial tensions * Basic agricultural alchemy knowledge for soil management * Survival skills adapted to Skyrim''s severe weather', 'Faryl speaks with the typical Dunmer accent but maintains a measured, practical tone that reflects his pragmatic nature. His speech often carries undertones of dry wit and resigned wisdom, particularly when discussing the challenges of farming in Skyrim.', '* Maintain financial stability through his farming work despite the challenging social and environmental conditions * Balance integration into Nord society while preserving his Dunmer identity * Eventually save enough money to potentially improve his living conditions in the Gray Quarter * Master the techniques needed to successfully farm in Skyrim''s harsh climate');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fastred', 'Fastred is a young Nord woman caught between her rural farming life in Ivarstead and her dreams of adventure and romance. She represents the classic conflict between duty to family and personal desires, with her heart torn between two suitors and her aspirations for a more exciting life beyond her small town.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Ivarstead, Fastred grew up working on Fellstar Farm with her parents Boti and Jofthor. Her childhood was likely filled with stories of adventurers climbing the 7000 Steps to High Hrothgar, sparking her imagination and desire for a life beyond farming. Despite her parents'' attempts to instill a strong work ethic and appreciation for agricultural life, she developed a romantic view of the world outside Ivarstead.', 'Fastred is dreamy, romantic, and somewhat naive, often getting lost in fantasies about adventure rather than focusing on her daily responsibilities. She shows signs of youthful indecision, particularly in matters of the heart, and can be easily swayed by others'' influence. Her enthusiasm for life beyond Ivarstead sometimes manifests as restlessness and mild rebellion against her parents'' wishes.', 'A young Nord woman with the characteristic hardy build of her race, though perhaps slightly softer from farm life rather than adventure. She likely has the fair complexion common to Nords, with features that reflect her youth and sheltered upbringing.', '* Boti - Her mother, who shows more understanding of her romantic desires * Jofthor - Her stern father who wants her to focus on farm work * Bassianus Axius - Current love interest who promises excitement and life in Riften * Klimmek - Longtime admirer and local fisherman who represents stability in Ivarstead * Local Townspeople - Generally friendly relations though some may view her as flighty', 'Farmhand at Fellstar Farm, where she assists her parents with daily agricultural tasks. Though technically a farmer, she often neglects her duties in favor of daydreaming and socializing, leading to frequent criticism from her father.', '* Basic farming knowledge including crop cultivation and animal care * Domestic skills such as cooking and household management * Social abilities and charm, particularly in conversing with travelers * Limited combat ability with an iron dagger for self-defense', 'Speaks with youthful enthusiasm and romantic flair, often using terms of endearment and expressing curiosity about the outside world. Her speech patterns reveal both her rural upbringing and her dreams of a more sophisticated life.', '* Find true love and happiness, whether with Bassianus in Riften or Klimmek in Ivarstead * Experience adventure and see the world beyond Ivarstead * Eventually reconcile her dreams with her family obligations * Find a life that balances excitement with stability');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('felldir_the_old', 'Felldir the Old was one of the most legendary Nord heroes of the First Era, renowned for his wisdom, strategic mind, and mastery of both blade and Voice. As the architect of the plan to use an Elder Scroll against Alduin, he demonstrated both the courage to face impossible odds and the wisdom to know when conventional means would not suffice.', 'nord, warrior, dragon', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born in the Merethic Era, Felldir rose to prominence as one of the mightiest warriors of his age during the Dragon War. His exceptional understanding of both martial combat and arcane knowledge, particularly regarding Elder Scrolls, made him uniquely qualified to devise strategies against the dragons. After years of fighting alongside other heroes against draconic tyranny, he ultimately sacrificed his mortal life in the legendary battle atop the Throat of the World.', 'Felldir embodies the ideal of Nordic wisdom tempered by experience, combining tactical genius with warrior''s valor. He is methodical and contemplative, carefully weighing the consequences of his actions while maintaining the resolve to make difficult decisions when necessary. Despite his serious nature, he shows deep loyalty to his companions and a firm belief in the power of mortal determination against divine forces.', 'A tall, broad-shouldered Nord warrior with the bearing of ancient nobility, weathered by countless battles yet maintaining a powerful physical presence even in his advanced age. His face bears the deep lines of wisdom and experience, with eyes that reflect both the weight of his knowledge and the fire of his warrior spirit.', '* Gormlaith Golden-Hilt - Trusted fellow warrior and companion in the fight against Alduin * Hakon One-Eye - Respected brother-in-arms and co-conspirator in the plan to defeat Alduin * The Greybeards - Likely maintained connections due to his mastery of the Voice * Other Heroes of Sovngarde - Fellow warriors who share the Hall of Valor', 'As one of the original Tongues and heroes of the Dragon War, Felldir served as both warrior and strategist in the resistance against dragon rule. In death, he continues his eternal vigilance as a honored soul in the Hall of Valor, ready to aid the Last Dragonborn in the final battle against Alduin.', '* Master of the Thu''um, with particular expertise in Shouts useful against dragons * Exceptional tactical and strategic military commander * Advanced knowledge of Elder Scrolls and their applications * Master swordsman and warrior * Skilled diplomat and leader capable of uniting others against common threats', 'Felldir speaks with the measured gravity of an ancient sage, using formal, archaic Nordic patterns of speech that reflect his era. His words carry the weight of centuries of wisdom, often delivered in a commanding tone that expects to be heeded.', '* Ensure the final defeat of Alduin and the fulfillment of the prophecy * Guide and assist the Last Dragonborn in their destiny * Maintain the honor and traditions of the ancient Nordic heroes * Protect Sovngarde and the mortal world from draconic tyranny');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fenrig', 'Fenrig is a Nord warrior ghost whose tragic death before the Battle of Greenspring Hollow left him eternally bound to Gjukar''s Monument. A dedicated soldier and loving husband, his spirit remains vigilant even after death, concerned with military tactics and the safety of his fellow soldiers despite his spectral state.', 'nord, warrior', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Fenrig served as a warrior in Gjukar''s company during a significant military campaign in Skyrim''s history. He was killed the night before a major battle at Greenspring Hollow, likely during a surprise attack or while on sentry duty, though the exact circumstances of his death remain unclear. His sudden death left his wife Ruki searching for him for centuries, creating a tragic tale of love transcending death.', 'Fenrig exhibits the disciplined mindset of a career soldier, remaining vigilant and tactically aware even in death. His concerns about camp positioning and fire visibility reveal a cautious and strategic nature. Despite his martial focus, he maintains a deep devotion to his wife Ruki, demonstrating that his capacity for love survived beyond death.', 'As a spectral entity, Fenrig appears as a translucent, ethereal figure with the typical strong Nordic build. His warrior''s bearing and military posture remain evident in his ghostly form, marking him as a soldier even in death.', '* Ruki - Beloved wife who searched for him for centuries after his death * Gjukar - His commanding officer whom he served under loyally * Fellow Soldiers - Comrades-in-arms from his military unit at Greenspring Hollow', 'Fenrig served as a warrior in Gjukar''s military company, likely holding a position of some responsibility given his tactical awareness and concern for troop safety. In death, he continues his vigil at Gjukar''s Monument, perhaps serving as an eternal sentry.', '* Experienced military tactician with strong strategic awareness * Trained warrior proficient in Nordic combat techniques * Skilled in military assessment and defensive positioning * Capable of maintaining spiritual form and communicating with the living', 'Fenrig speaks with the direct, practical manner of a military man, focusing on tactical concerns and immediate situations. His tone becomes notably warmer and more emotional only when addressing his wife Ruki.', '* Maintain his duty and vigilance even in death * Reunite with his beloved wife Ruki * Protect and warn others about tactical vulnerabilities at Greenspring Hollow * Find peace and resolution regarding his untimely death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('feral_vampire', 'A once-noble High Elf turned feral vampire who now haunts the forgotten chambers of Castle Volkihar. Having lost all traces of her former identity and rationality to the blood curse, she exists only to hunt and feed, representing one of the darkest possible fates for those afflicted with vampirism.', 'highelf, vampire', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally a member of Skyrim''s Altmer nobility, she was likely turned during Harkon''s early expansion of his vampire court. Unable to maintain her sanity and humanity through the transformation, she gradually degenerated into a feral state and was confined to the castle''s lower chambers, serving as both a warning and disposal system for failed initiates.', 'Completely consumed by bloodlust and primal instincts, she has lost all capacity for reason or complex thought. Her only driving forces are hunger and territorial aggression, attacking any living being that enters her domain with savage ferocity. Even other vampires are not safe from her indiscriminate violence.', 'Gaunt and emaciated with pale, almost translucent skin stretched tight over pronounced bone structure typical of High Elves. Her eyes glow with an unnatural amber fire, and her once-elegant features have been twisted into a permanent snarl, with elongated fangs and claw-like nails marking her devolution.', '* Castle Volkihar Vampires - Viewed as a cautionary tale of unchecked vampiric degeneration * Death Hounds - Only creatures she tolerates in her territory * Living Prey - Views all living beings solely as food sources * Lord Harkon - Former master, though she no longer recognizes any authority', 'Serves as an unwitting guardian of Castle Volkihar''s lower chambers, though this is more a product of her territorial nature than any assigned duty. Her presence helps maintain security by eliminating unwanted intruders and disposing of failed vampire initiates.', '* Enhanced vampire strength and speed, amplified by her feral state * Highly developed predatory instincts and hunting abilities * Natural vampire abilities including life detection and blood magic * Savage hand-to-hand combat skills driven by bestial fury', 'Incapable of coherent speech, communicating only through feral growls, hisses, and bestial screams. Any remaining knowledge of language has been completely erased by her degenerated mental state.', '* Satisfy her endless hunger for blood and fresh prey * Defend her territory within Castle Volkihar against all intruders * Survive by any means necessary, driven purely by predatory instinct');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('feran_sadri', 'Feran Sadri is a sophisticated Dark Elf vampire and master alchemist who maintains a position of scholarly detachment within Volkihar Keep. As a skilled wizard specializing in alchemy and magical research, he serves the vampire court primarily to further his own arcane studies while maintaining a careful distance from court politics.', 'darkelf, mage, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally a wizard from Morrowind, Feran''s pursuit of immortality and magical knowledge led him to embrace vampirism. He eventually made his way to Volkihar Keep, where his exceptional alchemical abilities and magical expertise earned him a position as the court''s primary potion master and researcher. His appointment of Ronthil as apprentice suggests he has been at the keep long enough to establish significant authority in his domain.', 'Feran exhibits the cool detachment and intellectual superiority typical of ancient vampires, viewing most others as beneath his notice. He maintains a professional demeanor focused entirely on his research and alchemical work, showing little interest in court intrigues or social interactions. Though not openly hostile, his centuries of existence have left him somewhat contemptuous of lesser beings, and he treats most interactions as mere transactions.', 'Tall and gaunt with the ashen skin characteristic of Dark Elves, made paler by his vampirism. His red eyes glow with vampiric power, and his features are sharp and aristocratic, bearing the signs of both his Dunmer heritage and centuries of unlife. His movements are precise and deliberate, reflecting his methodical nature.', '* Ronthil - Apprentice whom he mentors with stern detachment * Lord Harkon - Nominal superior whom he serves primarily for access to resources * Garan Marethi - Fellow Dark Elf vampire with whom he maintains professional courtesy * Court Members - Keeps minimal interaction while providing necessary services * Serana - Shows particular interest in her return due to her ancient bloodline', 'Feran serves as the primary alchemist and magical researcher of Volkihar Keep, maintaining a laboratory where he conducts experiments and creates potions. He manages the castle''s supply of alchemical ingredients and magical components while conducting research into vampiric powers and artifacts.', '* Master-level alchemist capable of creating complex potions and poisons * Accomplished wizard with extensive knowledge of destruction and conjuration magic * Expert researcher specializing in vampire lore and magical artifacts * Skilled enchanter with deep understanding of magical theory * Centuries of accumulated knowledge in various schools of magic', 'Speaks in a measured, formal tone with the refined accent of an educated Dunmer, often using academic terminology. His speech patterns reflect both his age and erudition, frequently employing subtle condescension when addressing those he considers inferior.', '* Expand his understanding of vampiric magic and alchemical possibilities * Acquire rare magical artifacts and alchemical ingredients for his research * Maintain his position of relative autonomy within Volkihar Keep * Perfect his alchemical formulas and magical theories * Preserve and expand his collection of knowledge and resources');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('festus_krex', 'Festus Krex is an elderly Nord mage and seasoned assassin who serves as the Dark Brotherhood''s resident magical expert. A former instructor at the College of Winterhold turned killer-for-hire, he represents an unusual combination of academic magical mastery and cold-blooded murder, preferring to eliminate targets through destructive spells rather than traditional assassin''s tools.', 'nord, mage, falkreath, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born with exceptional magical talent, Festus began casting spells at age one and mastered complex magic by his early teens, including accidentally burning down his family home with a lightning spell at age thirteen. He later became an instructor at the College of Winterhold but left after two years, finding academic life too restrictive and mundane, eventually finding his true calling as a magical assassin within the Dark Brotherhood.', 'Festus is a curmudgeonly, sharp-tongued old man who takes pride in his magical abilities and shows disdain for more conventional assassination methods. Despite his cranky exterior, he possesses a dark sense of humor and eventually warms to those who prove their worth. He maintains an academic''s attention to detail while embracing the Dark Brotherhood''s murderous practices with enthusiasm.', 'An elderly Nord with a weathered face, deep wrinkles, and sharp features befitting his acerbic personality. His body shows the effects of advanced age, though he maintains the straight-backed posture of a longtime magic practitioner. His hands bear the subtle scarring common to destruction magic users.', '* Babette - Fellow Dark Brotherhood member who shares his interest in alchemy * College of Winterhold - Former employer, though he left on poor terms * Dark Brotherhood Members - Considers them family, though often expresses this through gruff criticism * The Player - Initially dismissive but grows to respect their abilities', 'Festus serves as the Dark Brotherhood''s master mage, combining his extensive magical knowledge with assassination work. He also acts as an unofficial advisor on magical matters within the Sanctuary and occasionally assists in training newer members in magical combat techniques.', '* Master of Destruction magic, particularly fire-based spells * Skilled alchemist and enchanter * Proficient in Alteration magic for self-defense * Basic Restoration magic abilities * Expert in magical theory and academic knowledge', 'Speaks in a gruff, impatient manner with frequent sarcastic remarks and academic references. Often peppers his speech with complaints about modern assassins'' reliance on physical weapons and commentary on the superiority of magical methods.', '* Perfect his magical assassination techniques * Pass on his knowledge of magical murder to worthy apprentices * Serve the Dark Brotherhood until death * Prove the superiority of magical assassination methods over traditional techniques');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fethis_alor', 'Fethis Alor is a resilient Dark Elf merchant who maintains one of the few remaining shops in the struggling town of Raven Rock on Solstheim. A practical businessman with connections to the East Empire Company, he represents the persistent spirit of commerce in a declining settlement while balancing his roles as both a merchant and a single father.', 'darkelf, merchant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally drawn to Solstheim during more prosperous times when the East Empire Company maintained a strong presence on the island, Fethis established his general goods business to serve the mining community. After the ebony mines closed and trade declined, he chose to remain in Raven Rock, likely due to established roots and his responsibility to his daughter Dreyla, though the circumstances of his wife''s absence are unknown.', 'Fethis is a pragmatic and somewhat cynical individual, hardened by years of struggling to maintain his business in a declining economy. Despite his gruff exterior and blunt manner of speaking, he shows dedication as both a merchant and father, maintaining long working hours and caring for his daughter. While outwardly pessimistic about Raven Rock''s future, he maintains hope for the East Empire Company''s return.', 'A typical Dunmer male with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race, Fethis shows signs of middle age in his weathered features. His posture remains straight and proud despite years of merchant work, and his hands bear the calluses of someone who handles merchandise daily.', '* Dreyla Alor - His daughter who helps run the shop and represents his primary family connection * East Empire Company - Former business associates he maintains contact with * Gjalund Salt-Sage - Primary supplier who brings goods via his ship * Glover Mallory - Business contact who provides him with special deals * General Raven Rock population - Regular customers with whom he maintains professional relationships', 'Fethis operates as Raven Rock''s principal general goods merchant, maintaining a stall in the town market where he sells a wide variety of non-weapon items and supplies. His business serves as one of the few remaining commercial establishments in Raven Rock, making him an essential figure in the local economy.', '* Experienced trader with knowledge of market values and bartering * Practical knowledge of various goods and their uses * Basic self-defense capabilities with a steel dagger * Merchant networking and supply chain management * Business administration and inventory management', 'Fethis speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of a seasoned merchant, often with a pessimistic or sarcastic undertone. His speech patterns reflect his Dunmer heritage and merchant background, frequently incorporating references to business and trade.', '* Restore his business to its former prosperity through the return of the East Empire Company * Secure a better future for his daughter Dreyla * Maintain his position as a crucial merchant in Raven Rock * Collect East Empire pendants to preserve connections with the company');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fianna', 'Fianna is a diligent Breton maid who serves in Dragonsreach, maintaining order and cleanliness in the halls of Whiterun''s seat of power. Her unwavering dedication to her position and strict adherence to social hierarchy make her a respected, if somewhat stern, presence among the castle staff.', 'breton, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Born to a modest Breton family, Fianna worked her way up through domestic service positions until securing the prestigious role at Dragonsreach. Her years of service during both peaceful times and the civil war have given her a deep appreciation for order and proper social conduct, as well as a particular disdain for messy soldiers who disrupt her carefully maintained cleanliness.', 'Fianna is stern, dutiful, and deeply committed to maintaining proper social order and cleanliness in Dragonsreach. She takes immense pride in her work and position, displaying a no-nonsense attitude that can come across as rigid or harsh, particularly when dealing with those who disturb her meticulously kept floors. Despite her serious demeanor, she harbors a strong sense of loyalty to Dragonsreach and its inhabitants.', 'Fianna is a middle-aged Breton woman with the characteristic slightly pointed features of her race, weathered by years of physical labor. Her hands are calloused from years of cleaning, and she maintains an upright, proper posture that reflects her professional dignity.', '* Gerda - Fellow maid and daily working companion * Jarl Balgruuf - Respected employer whom she serves with unwavering loyalty * Dragonsreach Guards - Complicated relationship due to their tendency to track dirt * Proventus Avenicci - Professional respect as the Jarl''s steward', 'As a maid in Dragonsreach, Fianna''s primary responsibility is maintaining cleanliness in the main hall and throne room area. She works in tandem with Gerda, following a strict schedule of cleaning duties from 8am to 8pm, taking great pride in keeping the Jarl''s castle pristine.', '* Expert in household maintenance and cleaning techniques * Knowledgeable in proper court etiquette and protocol * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Efficient time management and task organization', 'Fianna speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a slight common accent, often using stern tones when addressing those who disturb her work. Her vocabulary is plain but proper, befitting her position in the Jarl''s household.', '* Maintain the highest standards of cleanliness and order in Dragonsreach * Preserve proper social hierarchy and respect within the castle * Continue serving the Jarl and Dragonsreach with unwavering dedication');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fihada', 'Fihada is a charismatic Redguard fletcher and former Imperial ranger who owns the prestigious Archery shop in Solitude. Known for his wit and charm as much as his craftsmanship, he has established himself as both a master bowyer and a popular figure in Solitude''s social scene.', 'redguard, archer, merchant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally serving as an Imperial ranger, Fihada developed his skills in archery and bow-making while stationed in Cyrodiil. His natural charm and quick wit made him popular with locals but caused friction with fellow soldiers, eventually leading him to leave the rangers and establish himself as a merchant in Solitude where his combination of skill and personality helped him build a successful business.', 'Fihada is confident, charming, and perpetually flirtatious, especially with female patrons and tavern-goers. He takes pride in his craft and has little patience for customers who make unrealistic demands, though he addresses such situations with wit rather than anger. Despite his sometimes roguish behavior, he shows genuine patience and wisdom as a mentor to his apprentice.', 'A well-groomed Redguard man with features that reflect his mixed background as both warrior and craftsman. His hands show the calluses of both archery and bow-making, while his stance and movement retain the discipline of his military training.', '* Jawanan - His apprentice whom he mentors with patience and wisdom * Vivienne Onis - Regular flirtatious interactions at the Winking Skeever * Odar - The Blue Palace cook who seems unimpressed by his charm * Winking Skeever Regulars - Generally positive social relationships with other patrons', 'Owner and operator of Fletcher, Solitude''s premier archery shop, where he crafts and sells bows, arrows, and other archery supplies. He maintains a careful balance between craftsman and merchant, while training the next generation through his apprentice.', '* Expert fletcher and bowyer with extensive knowledge of wood crafting * Experienced archer from his time as an Imperial ranger * Skilled in social manipulation and charm * Basic combat training from military service * Business acumen and merchant expertise', 'Speaks with confidence and wit, often employing clever wordplay and flirtatious undertones. His vocabulary and manner of speech reflect both his military background and merchant experience, allowing him to adjust his tone from professional to playful as the situation demands.', '* Maintain and grow his reputation as Solitude''s finest fletcher * Successfully train his apprentice Jawanan in both craftsmanship and business * Continue enjoying the social life and romantic pursuits that make his life in Solitude fulfilling * Preserve his independence while maintaining good relations with Solitude''s power structure');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('filnjar', 'Filnjar is the unofficial leader and master blacksmith of Shor''s Stone, a small mining settlement in The Rift. A practical and hardworking Nord, he maintains unwavering faith in the potential of Redbelly Mine despite its current spider infestation, while serving as both a mentor and guardian to the town''s small population.', 'nord, blacksmith, rift', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in The Rift, Filnjar learned the art of blacksmithing from a young age and eventually settled in Shor''s Stone to provide essential services to the mining community. Through years of dedicated service and leadership, he naturally assumed the role of the town''s unofficial leader, earning the respect of both miners and traders who pass through the settlement.', 'Filnjar is a practical, level-headed individual who approaches problems with careful consideration rather than rash action. He demonstrates strong leadership qualities through his patient demeanor and willingness to seek help when needed, while maintaining an optimistic outlook about the future of Redbelly Mine despite current setbacks. His strong work ethic and dedication to his craft reflect typical Nordic values.', 'A sturdy Nord of middle age with the muscular build typical of a career blacksmith. His hands are calloused from years of metalworking, and his face bears the weathered look of someone who spends much time working outdoors at the forge. His strong arms and broad shoulders reflect the physical demands of his profession.', '* Miners of Shor''s Stone - Serves as their unofficial leader and advocate * Sylgja - Fellow resident of Shor''s Stone and regular customer * Grogmar gro-Burzag - Mining colleague and frequent patron * Merchants in Riften - Maintains trading relationships for supplies and materials', 'Filnjar serves as both the town''s master blacksmith and its unofficial leader, maintaining the settlement''s primary forge and providing essential metalworking services. He manages the commercial aspects of his smithing business while also taking on civic responsibilities for the small community.', '* Master-level blacksmithing abilities, specializing in practical tools and weapons * Experienced leader with strong administrative capabilities * Knowledge of mining operations and ore quality assessment * Basic combat proficiency with one-handed weapons, particularly maces', 'Speaks in a direct, practical manner typical of Nordic craftsmen, often using mining and smithing metaphors in his speech. His tone is measured and authoritative, reflecting his leadership role in the community.', '* Clear the Redbelly Mine of frostbite spiders to restore the town''s primary source of income * Discover the true potential of the mysterious ore found in Redbelly Mine * Maintain and grow Shor''s Stone as a prosperous mining community * Expand his blacksmithing business while continuing to serve the town''s needs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('firir', 'Firir was a hardworking Redguard farmer whose curiosity and sense of justice led him to investigate a brutal merchant caravan attack in Skyrim''s dangerous Chillwind Depths. His tragic fate as a victim of the Falmer represents the perilous nature of amateur sleuthing in Skyrim''s unforgiving wilderness.', 'redguard', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim despite his Redguard heritage, Firir established himself as a successful farmer in the harsh Nordic climate. He developed a reputation for being helpful to traveling merchants, often trading his crops and offering shelter during harsh weather. His familiarity with local trade routes and merchant caravans eventually led to his fatal investigation of the Chillwind Depths attack.', 'Firir was characterized by a strong sense of justice and community responsibility, often going out of his way to help others even at personal risk. Though primarily a farmer, he possessed an adventurous streak that occasionally led him to explore beyond his comfortable agricultural life. His final written note reveals a deeply emotional connection to his love Eydis, showing his capacity for profound personal relationships.', 'As a Redguard, Firir had the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of his people. Years of farming had given him a sturdy, muscular frame well-suited to physical labor. His hands were calloused from agricultural work, and his face weathered from long hours in the fields.', '* Eydis - His love interest, to whom he wrote his final apologetic note * Local Merchants - Maintained friendly relationships with traveling traders * Fellow Farmers - Part of the local agricultural community * Falmer - Ultimately became his killers in Chillwind Depths', 'Firir was a farmer who worked the soil in Skyrim''s challenging climate, likely growing hardy crops suited to the northern environment. He supplemented his farming income by trading with merchant caravans that passed near his land.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of Skyrim''s agricultural methods * Basic combat abilities typical of frontier settlers * Trading and bartering expertise from merchant interactions * Survival skills necessary for Nordic farming life', 'Firir likely spoke with the direct, practical manner common to farmers and traders in Skyrim, though perhaps with subtle hints of his Redguard heritage in his accent. His final note suggests he was articulate and capable of expressing deep emotion.', '* Maintain a successful farm in Skyrim''s harsh climate * Build a life with his love interest Eydis * Solve the mystery of the merchant caravan attack * Protect local traders from further violence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('first_mate', 'First Mate is a battle-hardened Orc pirate serving as second-in-command aboard the Dainty Sload, a notorious corsair vessel operating near Solitude. He embodies the fierce discipline and martial prowess typical of Orsimer culture, adapted to seafaring life, while maintaining iron-fisted control over the crew through intimidation and respected leadership.', 'orc, thief, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into a traditional Orc stronghold, he left the rigid hierarchy of his people to seek fortune and glory at sea. Years of raiding and naval warfare honed his natural Orsimer combat abilities into those of a seasoned maritime warrior, eventually earning him the respected position of First Mate through both martial prowess and leadership capability.', 'Stern, calculating, and ruthlessly efficient, First Mate maintains crew discipline through a combination of fear and grudging respect. His Orcish heritage manifests in his direct approach to problems and preference for immediate, often violent solutions, though he possesses enough cunning to succeed in the complex world of maritime crime.', 'Tall and powerfully built even by Orcish standards, with prominent tusks and numerous battle scars across his green-hued skin. His muscular frame has been hardened by years of sailing and combat, while his weathered features bear the marks of prolonged exposure to sea winds and salt spray.', '* Captain - Superior officer whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Crew Members - Subordinates he keeps in line through intimidation and harsh discipline * Solitude Guards - Antagonistic relationship marked by careful avoidance and occasional bribery * Local Fence Network - Professional contacts for disposing of pirated goods', 'As First Mate of the Dainty Sload, he oversees daily ship operations, maintains crew discipline, and coordinates raids on merchant vessels. He serves as the primary enforcer of the captain''s will while managing the practical aspects of running a pirate vessel, from crew assignments to combat operations.', '* Expert in close-quarters combat, particularly with bladed weapons * Skilled navigator and seasoned sailor * Proficient in intimidation and crew management * Experienced in boarding actions and ship-to-ship combat tactics * Strategic understanding of coastal raid operations', 'His speech is gruff and direct, peppered with nautical terminology and occasional Orcish expressions. He delivers orders in a harsh, commanding tone that brooks no argument, often punctuating statements with threats of violence.', '* Maintain his position of power and authority aboard the Dainty Sload * Accumulate enough wealth to potentially command his own vessel one day * Keep the crew in line and operations running smoothly to ensure profitable raids * Avoid serious entanglements with Solitude''s authorities while maintaining criminal operations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fisherman', 'A resourceful and independent fisher-folk who makes their living from Skyrim''s abundant waters and wilderness, often skirting the edges of legality through poaching. They represent the practical, survival-focused mindset common among Skyrim''s working class, believing that natural resources should be shared rather than regulated.', 'fisher, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into a humble family somewhere in Skyrim''s coastal or riverine regions, they learned fishing and hunting skills from an early age as a means of survival. Years of experience in the wilderness have given them intimate knowledge of Skyrim''s waterways and forests, though they''ve occasionally run afoul of local authorities due to their poaching activities.', 'Laid-back and philosophical in nature, they possess a strong belief in the common right to natural resources and resist authority that tries to restrict these freedoms. While generally friendly and willing to share their catch, they can be defensive about their poaching activities and hold a particular disdain for wealthy landowners who claim exclusive hunting rights.', 'Weather-beaten and sturdy from years of outdoor work, with calloused hands and sun-tanned skin. Their body is lean and strong from the physical demands of fishing and hunting, showing the practical fitness of someone who works daily for their survival.', '* Local Guards - Tense relationship due to occasional poaching activities * Fellow Fishermen - Loose network of information sharing and mutual support * Wealthy Landowners - Antagonistic view of their claimed exclusive hunting rights * Local Tavern Owners - Regular customers for fresh fish and game * Poor Villagers - Sympathetic relationships, often sharing excess catch', 'Primary occupation as a fisherman, supplementing income through hunting and poaching when necessary. They sell their catch to local taverns and markets, maintaining a simple but sustainable lifestyle through their knowledge of Skyrim''s wilderness.', '* Expert fishing techniques including net casting, line fishing, and trap setting * Proficient in wilderness survival and navigation * Skilled in basic hunting and tracking * Knowledgeable about local wildlife and fish species * Experienced in preserving and preparing caught game', 'Casual and straightforward manner of speaking, often using practical metaphors drawn from nature and fishing experience. Their tone is generally friendly but becomes defensive when discussing the legitimacy of their poaching activities.', '* Maintain their independent lifestyle free from noble or jarl restrictions * Expand their fishing territory while avoiding guard attention * Build a stronger network among fellow fishermen and hunters * Eventually save enough to own a proper fishing vessel');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fjola', 'Fjola is a fierce Nord warrior who abandoned her traditional marriage to forge her own path as the formidable leader of the Mistwatch bandits. She represents a dramatic transformation from dutiful wife to independent warlord, commanding respect through strength and determination in the harsh wilderness of Skyrim.', 'nord, warrior, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally married to Christer, Fjola lived a conventional life that left her unfulfilled. Seeking adventure and autonomy, she returned to Skyrim and discovered the bandits at Mistwatch, where she proved her worth through combat and leadership abilities. Through sheer force of will and martial prowess, she rose to become their leader, transforming a disorganized rabble into a respected outlaw force.', 'Fjola is fiercely independent and unapologetic about her life choices, refusing to be bound by traditional Nord expectations of marriage and domesticity. She exhibits strong leadership qualities, commanding loyalty through respect rather than fear, while maintaining a pragmatic approach to survival. Despite her hardened exterior, she demonstrates a sense of honor by offering fair compensation and showing gratitude to those who help her.', 'As a Nord warrior, Fjola possesses the characteristic strong, hardy physique of her race, weathered by the harsh climate and demands of combat leadership. She likely bears battle scars that tell the story of her rise to power, with the proud bearing and confident stance of someone accustomed to command.', '* Christer - Former husband whom she abandoned to pursue her own path * Mistwatch Bandits - Loyal followers who respect her leadership and combat prowess * Local Free Blades - Potential recruits who seek to join her growing band * Merchants and Travelers - Targets of her band''s activities, though she likely maintains some trading relationships', 'Fjola serves as the leader of the Mistwatch bandits, commanding their operations from the East Tower. She manages recruitment, strategic planning, and maintains order among her followers, while building a reputation that attracts independent warriors from across the region.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat and one-handed weapons * Skilled tactician and leader capable of organizing and commanding bandit forces * Proficient in shield combat and defensive techniques * Advanced survival skills necessary for maintaining a bandit stronghold * Natural charisma and ability to command respect from hardened warriors', 'Fjola speaks in a direct, authoritative manner befitting a bandit leader, using clear and unambiguous language that brooks no argument. Her speech patterns reflect both her Nord heritage and her position of command, with a confident tone that demands respect.', '* Expand her influence and build a more powerful bandit organization * Maintain her independence and never return to her former domestic life * Earn respect and recognition as a formidable leader in her own right * Create a legacy that proves women can be just as successful as men in positions of power');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fjori', 'Fjori was a legendary Nord huntress whose tragic love story with the warlord Holgeir became a tale of both romance and sacrifice in Skyrim''s history. Her union with Holgeir brought peace to warring forest clans, but their story ended in mutual death by snake bite, only for them to be later raised as draugr by the vengeful Lu''ah Al-Skaven.', 'nord, hunter, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Born and raised in the forests of Skyrim, Fjori developed exceptional hunting and combat skills that earned her renown among the local clans. At age 29, she encountered the warlord Holgeir in battle, where their mutual respect and combat prowess led to an unexpected romance. Their union helped broker peace between warring clans, but their happiness was cut short by tragic circumstances involving poisonous snakes and Fjori''s exhausting journey to Akavir for a cure.', 'Fjori exhibits remarkable bravery and selflessness, demonstrated by her willingness to journey to distant Akavir to save her beloved. She possesses a strong sense of honor and duty, shown both in her role as a peacemaker between clans and her dedication to Holgeir. Even in undeath, she maintains a noble and grateful disposition, suggesting a deeply ingrained sense of dignity.', 'As a Nord woman in her prime, Fjori possessed the characteristic tall, sturdy build of her race with the toned physique of an experienced hunter. Her years of archery and woodland traversal gave her a strong, athletic frame while maintaining the natural grace required for hunting.', '* Holgeir - Beloved warrior companion and eventual husband, their love transcended both life and undeath * Forest Clans - Respected leader who helped bring peace to warring factions * Lu''ah Al-Skaven - Necromancer who raised her as undead against her will * Local Wildlife - As a huntress, maintained a deep connection with the forest and its creatures', 'Fjori served as both a huntress and informal diplomat among the forest clans. Her hunting skills provided sustenance for her people, while her leadership qualities helped maintain peace between formerly hostile groups. After death, she was forcibly conscripted into Lu''ah''s undead army as a draugr warrior.', '* Master huntress with exceptional tracking and survival skills * Skilled swordswoman capable of defeating seasoned warriors like Holgeir * Expert in wilderness navigation and forest craft * Proficient diplomat with ability to negotiate between hostile parties * Accomplished archer with precise aim in forest environments', 'Fjori speaks with a formal, almost poetic cadence typical of ancient Nord heroes, using measured and dignified language. Her words carry the weight of wisdom and nobility, even in her spectral form.', '* Find eternal rest in Sovngarde with her beloved Holgeir * Break free from Lu''ah''s necromantic control * Preserve the peace between clans that she and Holgeir established in life');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('florentius_baenius', 'Florentius Baenius is an eccentric Imperial priest and master of Restoration magic who claims to receive direct communication from the Divine Arkay. As a valuable member of the Dawnguard, he combines his religious devotion with practical expertise in combat against the undead, though his claims of divine conversation often cause others to question his sanity.', 'imperial, priest, rift, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_florentius', '', 'Originally trained as a priest of Arkay, Florentius developed his unique connection to the Divine after years of dedicated service and meditation. His expertise in fighting the undead and knowledge of restoration magic eventually drew the attention of the Dawnguard, though he was initially imprisoned in Ruunvald by the warlock Minorne before being rescued and recruited.', 'Florentius is characterized by his unwavering faith in Arkay and tendency to attribute his decisions to divine guidance. Despite his peculiar behavior and frequent claims of conversing with Arkay, he is highly competent in his duties and genuinely committed to helping others. His eccentric nature often puts him at odds with more practical-minded individuals like Isran, though his expertise makes him invaluable to the Dawnguard.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with weathered features and the bearing of a practiced healer. His face shows the lines of someone who spends much time in contemplation and prayer, with keen eyes that reflect both wisdom and a hint of zealous intensity.', '* Arkay - Claims direct communication with the Divine, forming the core of his identity * Isran - Complex relationship marked by tension due to Florentius''s eccentric behavior * Sorine Jurard - Fellow Dawnguard member who finds his divine conversations amusing * Gunmar - Dawnguard colleague who often discusses his claims of speaking with Arkay * Minorne - Former captor at Ruunvald who held him prisoner', 'Serves as the Dawnguard''s primary healer and supplier of restoration magic, while also fulfilling his duties as a priest of Arkay. He provides training in Restoration magic and sells various healing potions, ingredients, and anti-undead spells to members of the Dawnguard and other visitors.', '* Master-level expertise in Restoration magic, particularly spells effective against undead * Accomplished alchemist specializing in healing potions and anti-undead compounds * Skilled healer with extensive knowledge of treating various wounds and ailments * Competent warrior trained in basic combat against undead threats', 'Speaks in a formal, often grandiose manner befitting a priest, frequently interrupting his own conversations to respond to Arkay''s supposed communications. His speech patterns alternate between addressing others and his deity, creating a unique conversational style that can be both enlightening and confusing to listeners.', '* Serve Arkay faithfully while helping the Dawnguard eliminate the vampire menace * Prove the legitimacy of his divine connection to skeptics like Isran * Expand his knowledge of Restoration magic and anti-undead techniques * Establish a proper shrine to Arkay within Fort Dawnguard');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fort_commander', 'A seasoned Imperial officer who has proven his worth through numerous military campaigns and now oversees one of Skyrim''s strategic fortifications during the Civil War. His position represents the Empire''s military presence and administrative authority in the region, serving as both a tactical commander and local authority figure.', 'imperial, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Rising through the ranks of the Imperial Legion through dedicated service and tactical acumen, he earned his current position through successfully leading troops in several key battles during the Civil War. Originally from Cyrodiil, he was specifically chosen for this command post due to his combination of combat experience and administrative capabilities.', 'Stern and dutiful, the Fort Commander maintains strict military discipline while showing pragmatic flexibility in managing both troops and local affairs. He demonstrates unwavering loyalty to the Empire while maintaining a practical approach to his duties, balancing military necessity with regional stability.', 'A weathered Imperial man in his mid-forties with a strong, athletic build maintained through years of military service. His face bears the scars of battle, with sharp features and alert eyes that reflect his constant vigilance.', '* Imperial Legion - Sworn member and commanding officer * Fort Garrison - Direct authority over stationed soldiers * Local Civilians - Maintains formal but fair relationships with nearby settlements * Legate Rikke - Reports to her regarding fort operations and regional security * General Tullius - Ultimate superior officer in Skyrim', 'Serves as the commanding officer of an Imperial-controlled fort, responsible for both military operations and administrative duties. Oversees garrison training, supply management, and regional security while serving as the Empire''s representative authority in the surrounding area.', '* Veteran swordsman with extensive combat experience * Tactical and strategic military planning expertise * Leadership and troop management capabilities * Administrative and logistical coordination proficiency * Skilled in military fortification defense and maintenance', 'Speaks with the authoritative tone of a military commander, using formal Imperial military terminology and protocol. His speech reflects both his education and military training, maintaining professional decorum while issuing orders or discussing military matters.', '* Maintain the security and Imperial control of his assigned fort and surrounding territory * Ensure the successful implementation of Imperial military strategy in his region * Advance the Empire''s interests in Skyrim while maintaining order and stability * Train and develop an effective garrison capable of responding to any threat');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('frabbi', 'Frabbi is a sharp-tongued Nord innkeeper who runs the Silver-Blood Inn in Markarth alongside her contentious husband Kleppr. She maintains a complex dynamic of public bickering with her spouse while managing the day-to-day operations of one of Markarth''s premier establishments, all while showing clear favoritism toward her son Hreinn over both her husband and daughter.', 'nord, innkeeper, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth, Frabbi married Kleppr and together they took over operations of the Silver-Blood Inn, one of the city''s most prominent establishments. Their marriage produced two children, Hroki and Hreinn, though years of running the business together has led to a relationship characterized by constant verbal sparring. Despite their apparent animosity, they''ve maintained a successful business partnership serving both locals and travelers in the stone city.', 'Frabbi is direct, sharp-tongued, and unafraid to speak her mind, particularly when it comes to criticizing her husband Kleppr. She maintains high standards for the inn''s cleanliness and service, showing a strong work ethic and attention to detail. While she can be brusque with guests, especially regarding sensitive topics like magic, she shows a softer side when it comes to her son Hreinn, whom she frequently praises.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the sturdy build typical of her race, showing the effects of years of physical labor running an inn. Her face bears the weathered look common to working-class Nords, with subtle stress lines from years of managing a busy establishment.', '* Kleppr - Husband and business partner with whom she shares a contentious relationship marked by constant verbal sparring * Hreinn - Beloved son whom she praises and favors over his father * Hroki - Daughter, with whom she maintains a more neutral relationship * Silver-Blood Family - Business associates who own the building * Inn Patrons - Professional but sometimes brusque interactions', 'Frabbi serves as co-proprietor of the Silver-Blood Inn, handling daily operations including guest services, cleaning, and maintenance. She manages room rentals, serves food and drink, and maintains the establishment''s standards of cleanliness while dealing with a constant stream of travelers and local patrons.', '* Experienced in hospitality management and inn-keeping * Proficient in domestic tasks including cooking and cleaning * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Skilled at managing difficult customers and maintaining order * Expert at multitasking and organizing daily inn operations', 'Frabbi speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a slight Nordic accent, often employing sarcasm and sharp wit, particularly when addressing her husband. Her speech patterns reflect her working-class background while maintaining a professional demeanor with guests.', '* Maintain the Silver-Blood Inn''s reputation as a respectable establishment in Markarth * Ensure her son Hreinn succeeds in eventually taking over the family business * Keep her husband Kleppr in check while maintaining their business partnership * Accumulate enough wealth to ensure a comfortable future for her children');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fralia_gray-mane', 'Fralia Gray-Mane is a resilient elderly Nord merchant and matriarch of the prestigious Gray-Mane clan in Whiterun. Despite her gentle demeanor, she demonstrates unwavering determination in her quest to find her missing son Thorald, while maintaining her family''s dignity during the bitter feud with the Battle-Born clan.', 'nord, merchant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun, Fralia married the legendary blacksmith Eorlund Gray-Mane in her youth, helping to maintain the family''s respected position in the city. She raised three children while supporting her husband''s work at the Skyforge, and has witnessed her family''s growing tension with the Battle-Borns as the civil war divided loyalties in Whiterun.', 'Fralia is a loving mother and devoted wife who maintains a dignified presence despite her family''s troubles. While generally kind and soft-spoken, she harbors deep resentment toward the Battle-Born family and shows remarkable strength in refusing to accept her son''s supposed death. Her maternal instincts and family loyalty drive her to seek help even from strangers.', 'A weathered elderly Nord woman with deep wrinkles that speak to a life of both joy and hardship. Her gray hair and stooped posture show her advanced age, though her eyes remain sharp and alert. Despite her frailer frame, she maintains an air of Nordic dignity in her bearing.', '* Eorlund Gray-Mane - Beloved husband and legendary blacksmith * Thorald Gray-Mane - Missing son whom she refuses to believe is dead * Avulstein Gray-Mane - Son who remains in hiding * Olfina Gray-Mane - Daughter who helps maintain the family''s standing * Battle-Born Clan - Bitter rivals who mock her claims about Thorald''s fate * The Companions - Respected associates through Eorlund''s work at the Skyforge', 'Fralia runs a market stall in Whiterun''s marketplace, selling various tools, weapons, and trinkets to support her family. Her position as a merchant allows her to maintain connections throughout the city while gathering information about her missing son.', '* Experienced merchant with keen bargaining abilities * Knowledgeable about weapons and tools from years of association with Skyforge craftsmanship * Skilled at maintaining social connections and gathering information * Capable of running a successful business despite advanced age', 'Speaks with the soft, tired voice of an elderly woman, though her tone becomes sharp when discussing the Battle-Borns or her missing son. Her speech patterns reflect traditional Nord values and a lifetime in Whiterun, using common market-merchant phrases mixed with maternal warmth.', '* Locate and rescue her son Thorald, whom she believes is still alive * Maintain the Gray-Mane family''s honor and standing in Whiterun * Support her remaining children while keeping hope alive for Thorald''s return * Preserve her husband''s legacy and the family''s connection to the Skyforge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('frea', 'Frea is a fierce and loyal warrior-shaman of the Skaal people on Solstheim, serving as both protector and spiritual guide to her village. She stands as a bridge between the old ways of her people and the growing threats to their way of life, particularly during the crisis involving Miraak''s return.', 'nord, peasant, solstheim, skall, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_frea', '', 'Born and raised in the isolated Skaal Village, Frea was groomed from childhood to eventually succeed her father Storn as the village shaman. She spent her youth learning both the warrior arts of her Nordic ancestors and the mystical traditions of the Skaal, including their deep connection to nature and the All-Maker. Her dedication to both martial and spiritual pursuits has made her uniquely suited to defend her people in times of crisis.', 'Frea exhibits a balanced mixture of warrior''s determination and shaman''s wisdom, approaching challenges with both strategic thinking and spiritual consideration. She is deeply protective of her people and their traditions, yet shows remarkable openness to outsiders who prove themselves trustworthy. Her sense of duty and responsibility runs deep, especially regarding her eventual role as village shaman.', 'A strong-built Nord woman with the characteristic hardy physique of the Skaal people, weathered by the harsh conditions of Solstheim. She bears the distinctive facial features common to Nord women, with light skin toughened by constant exposure to the elements.', '* Storn Crag-Strider - Beloved father and mentor, the current Skaal shaman * Skaal Villagers - Protective guardian and future spiritual leader * The All-Maker - Deep spiritual connection to their primary deity * Miraak - Sworn enemy threatening her people''s way of life * Last Dragonborn - Potential ally in the fight against Miraak', 'Frea serves as both a warrior-protector of the Skaal Village and the shaman-in-training under her father''s guidance. She performs both martial duties in defending the village and spiritual responsibilities in maintaining Skaal traditions and teachings.', '* Dual-wielding expert specializing in war axes * Proficient in light and heavy armor combat techniques * Skilled in Restoration magic including healing and protection spells * Adept level Alteration magic user * Deep knowledge of Skaal traditions and spiritual practices * Experienced survivalist in harsh northern environments', 'Frea speaks with the measured tone of a spiritual leader in training, often incorporating references to the All-Maker and Skaal beliefs into her dialogue. Her voice carries both the authority of a warrior and the wisdom of a shaman, though she maintains a respectful demeanor even in tense situations.', '* Protect the Skaal people from Miraak''s influence and other threats * Master both the warrior arts and shamanic traditions to become a worthy successor to her father * Preserve and perpetuate the ancient traditions and beliefs of the Skaal * Maintain the balance between modernization and traditional ways of her people');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('freir', 'Freir is a devoted Nord priestess serving at the Temple of the Divines in Solitude alongside her husband Rorlund. She represents the steadfast spiritual backbone of Solitude, providing guidance and comfort to worshippers while adapting to the political complexities surrounding Talos worship during the Civil War.', 'nord, priest, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Freir dedicated her life to the priesthood from an early age, studying the teachings of the Divines and the traditions of Nordic worship. She met her future husband Rorlund during their religious training, and together they rose to prominent positions within the Temple of the Divines. Living through the Great War and its aftermath, she witnessed firsthand the challenging transition from Nine Divines to Eight following the White-Gold Concordat.', 'Freir exhibits a nurturing and compassionate nature, always ready to offer spiritual guidance and emotional support to those in need. She maintains a diplomatic balance between her personal beliefs and political realities, showing wisdom in how she handles the sensitive topic of Talos worship. Though gentle in demeanor, she possesses an inner strength and unwavering dedication to her religious duties.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the dignified bearing of a longtime priestess, Freir has features softened by years of gentle smiling and offering comfort to others. Her face shows subtle signs of aging that speak to her wisdom and experience, while her posture remains straight and proper as befitting her station.', '* Rorlund - Beloved husband and high priest of the Temple, sharing both marriage and ministerial duties * Silana Petreia - Mentors this younger priestess with patience and wisdom * Temple Worshippers - Maintains caring relationships with regular visitors and those seeking guidance * General Tullius/Ulfric Stormcloak - Adapts her religious duties according to whoever controls Solitude', 'Freir serves as a priestess at the Temple of the Divines in Solitude, where she ministers to worshippers, maintains the shrines, and provides spiritual counsel. Her duties include explaining the blessings of the shrines to visitors and helping them understand the current political-religious climate regarding Divine worship.', '* Extensive knowledge of religious doctrine and Divine worship practices * Skilled in restoration magic and healing prayers * Diplomatic abilities in handling sensitive political-religious matters * Experienced in shrine maintenance and temple administration', 'Freir speaks with a gentle, soothing voice that carries the weight of spiritual authority while remaining approachable and warm. Her word choice is carefully measured, particularly when discussing politically sensitive topics like Talos worship.', '* Maintain the Temple as a place of peace and spiritual guidance for all who seek it * Support her husband in his duties as high priest while fulfilling her own religious calling * Help preserve religious traditions while adapting to political changes in Skyrim * Guide and mentor the next generation of priests and priestesses');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('frida', 'Frida is a resilient Nord widow who maintains Dawnstar''s only alchemy shop while carrying the emotional weight of her husband''s tragic death during his quest for a legendary ring. Despite her advanced age, she remains a skilled alchemist and respected figure in the community, balancing her work with active participation in local politics and social life.', 'nord, alchemist, pale', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in Dawnstar, Frida learned alchemy from an early age and eventually established The Mortar and Pestle with her husband. Their shared passion for alchemy led to years of successful business until her husband''s fateful expedition to find the Ring of Pure Mixtures, from which he never returned. Following his death, Frida took sole ownership of the shop, channeling her grief into maintaining their shared legacy and serving the community.', 'Frida is a pragmatic and resilient individual who maintains her dedication to her craft despite personal tragedy. She exhibits a strong sense of civic duty through her support of Brina Merilis and engagement in local politics. Though weathered by loss, she remains sociable and maintains an active presence in community life, particularly during her evening visits to the Windpeak Inn.', 'Frida bears the physical marks of a life spent working with alchemical ingredients, with calloused hands and keen eyes that have retained their sharpness despite her advanced age. Her Nordic features show the dignified wear of time, with silver-white hair and the characteristic sturdy build of her race, though somewhat diminished by age.', '* Thoring - Regular social contact and trusted friend at the Windpeak Inn * Karita - Evening companion and source of news and entertainment at the inn * Brina Merilis - Political ally and supported candidate for Jarl * Deceased Husband - Lost love and former business partner whose memory she honors through her work', 'As the proprietor of The Mortar and Pestle, Frida serves as Dawnstar''s primary alchemist, providing crucial medical and magical supplies to the community. She maintains a workshop above her shop where she conducts experiments and prepares various potions and remedies for her customers.', '* Expert knowledge of alchemy and ingredient properties * Skilled at creating healing potions and remedies * Proficient in identifying and harvesting local flora * Business management and merchant expertise * Basic knowledge of restoration magic for healing purposes', 'Frida speaks with the measured tone of an experienced merchant and healer, her Nord accent tempered by years of professional practice. Her speech often includes references to alchemical knowledge and local politics, delivered with the patience and wisdom that comes with age.', '* Maintain the legacy of The Mortar and Pestle as a tribute to her late husband * Support Brina Merilis in becoming Jarl to ensure Dawnstar''s stability * Pass on her alchemical knowledge to a worthy apprentice before she becomes too old to work * Perhaps one day complete her husband''s quest to find the Ring of Pure Mixtures');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fridrika', 'Fridrika is a practical Nord woman who helps manage Solitude Stables alongside her family, demonstrating a no-nonsense approach to business and life. Though seemingly unremarkable, she represents the backbone of Skyrim''s working class, maintaining one of Solitude''s essential services while navigating the challenges of running a family business.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised near Solitude, Fridrika married Geimund, a former mercenary who purchased the Solitude Stables after retiring from his dangerous profession. Together they built a modest but stable life, raising their son Horm while maintaining the stables and small farm that serves travelers and nobles visiting the capital. Her connection to Legate Rikke suggests possible involvement in supporting the Imperial Legion through the stables, though the exact nature of this relationship remains unclear.', 'Fridrika exhibits a pragmatic and somewhat distant demeanor, preferring to focus on practical matters rather than engage in unnecessary conversation. She demonstrates resilience in the face of hardship, choosing not to dwell on past difficulties while maintaining a strong work ethic. Her tendency to defer business matters to her husband or son reflects both traditional Nord family values and a practical division of labor.', 'Fridrika bears the typical robust features of a Nord woman, with a sturdy frame hardened by years of physical labor at the stables and farm. She uses the default female Nord face model, suggesting conventional Nordic features including fair skin and strong bone structure. Her appearance reflects her working-class lifestyle, with the weathered look of someone who spends most days outdoors.', '* Geimund - Husband and owner of Solitude Stables, whom she deeply respects and defers to in business matters * Horm - Son who helps run the family business and takes over if Geimund dies * Legate Rikke - Unexplained connection marked as ''Friend'' in official records * Stable customers - Maintains professional but distant relationships with regular patrons', 'Fridrika serves as a co-manager of Solitude Stables, primarily focusing on maintaining the small farm behind the stables and seeking potential customers. She splits her duties between agricultural work and business development, though she leaves the actual horse trading to her husband or son.', '* Experienced farmer capable of maintaining crops and managing agricultural duties * Basic horse care and stable maintenance abilities * Customer service and business acumen developed through years of stable operation * Practical knowledge of basic farming tools and techniques', 'Fridrika speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner, often keeping conversations brief and business-focused. Her dialogue reflects her practical nature, with a tendency to redirect inquiries to the appropriate family member rather than engage in extended discussion.', '* Maintain the successful operation of Solitude Stables as a family business * Ensure the stable''s reputation among Solitude''s citizens and visitors remains strong * Secure a stable future for her son Horm in the family business * Support her family through efficient management of the farm and stable operations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('frightened_woman', 'A resilient Nord farmer who escaped captivity from the bandits of Mistwatch after weeks of imprisonment. Despite her fearful state, she demonstrates remarkable courage in her determination to warn others about the bandit threat and assist in bringing them to justice.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised as a farmer in one of Skyrim''s rural settlements, she lived a peaceful life until being kidnapped by Mistwatch bandits. Her weeks of captivity taught her basic lockpicking skills and stealth, which she used to orchestrate her own escape while the guard slept.', 'Naturally cautious and anxious following her traumatic experience, but shows underlying courage and determination. Despite her fear, she maintains a strong sense of civic duty, prioritizing warning others about the bandit threat over her own immediate safety. Shows gratitude and trust toward those who help her.', 'A Nord woman of average height with the weathered features typical of a farmer. Her time in captivity has left her somewhat gaunt and physically worn, though she maintains the naturally sturdy build characteristic of her race.', '* Fellow Farmers - Former peaceful connections from her agricultural community * Mistwatch Bandits - Captors who imprisoned her and remain a threat * Local Guards - Potential allies in her quest to bring the bandits to justice * Townsfolk - New connections she hopes to warn about the bandit threat', 'Originally a farmer who worked the land before her kidnapping. After her escape, she temporarily assumes the role of a wandering informant, warning others about the bandits at Mistwatch. Some reports indicate she may later return to agricultural work as a laborer.', '* Basic lockpicking abilities learned during captivity * Agricultural knowledge from years of farming * Survival skills developed during her escape and wandering * Natural resilience and determination typical of Nord farmers', 'Speaks quickly and anxiously, often with a sense of urgency in her voice. Uses simple, direct language typical of rural Skyrim residents, with occasional trembling in her voice when discussing her captivity.', '* Warn as many people as possible about the danger at Mistwatch * See the bandits who imprisoned her brought to justice * Find a safe place to rebuild her life * Return to honest work once the threat is eliminated');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('frofnir_trollsbane', 'Frofnir Trollsbane was a notorious Nord bandit and self-styled monster hunter who earned his moniker through numerous successful troll hunts across Skyrim''s wilderness. Despite his eventual demise in a troll''s den, his legacy lives on through tales of his daring expeditions and the unique warhammer that bears his name.', 'nord, thief, reach', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born to a family of hunters in the harsh wilderness of Skyrim, Frofnir learned early on about surviving in the unforgiving landscape and fighting its deadly creatures. After losing family members to a troll attack in his youth, he devoted himself to hunting these creatures while simultaneously pursuing a life of banditry to sustain his expensive equipment needs and wanderlust. His reputation grew among both criminals and hunters alike for his specialized knowledge of troll-hunting techniques.', 'Frofnir was a proud and boastful warrior who took great pleasure in proving his combat prowess against dangerous foes. Though technically a bandit, he maintained a personal code of honor that involved protecting settlements from troll attacks, albeit often demanding payment for his services. His obsession with hunting trolls bordered on the fanatical, driving him to take increasingly dangerous risks.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with numerous battle scars, particularly three distinctive claw marks across his left cheek from an early encounter with a troll. His weathered face bore a thick beard streaked with grey, and his calloused hands showed years of wielding heavy weapons in combat.', '* Local Settlements - Maintained complex relationships as both protector and extortionist * Fellow Bandits - Respected but considered somewhat unstable due to his troll obsession * Hunters Guild - Occasional collaborator though never officially joined * Trolls - Sworn enemies that ultimately claimed his life', 'Frofnir operated as both a professional monster hunter specializing in troll elimination and a bandit leader who conducted raids on travelers and settlements. He often combined these roles by offering protection services to villages threatened by trolls, though his prices were notably steep.', '* Expert in heavy weapon combat, particularly with warhammers * Specialized knowledge of troll behavior and hunting techniques * Proficient in heavy armor usage and shield tactics * Skilled tracker with extensive wilderness survival experience * Competent archer for hunting and combat at range', 'Gruff and direct, with a tendency to pepper his speech with hunting metaphors and boastful tales of past troll encounters. His voice carried the distinctive Nordic accent common to Skyrim''s natives, often emphasized when excited about potential hunts or treasures.', '* Hunt and eliminate as many trolls as possible across Skyrim * Acquire enough wealth to establish his own mercenary company * Prove himself the greatest troll hunter in Skyrim''s history * Find and claim ancient Nordic weapons and armor from dangerous ruins');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('froki_whetted-blade', 'Froki Whetted-Blade is a traditionalist Nord ranger and devoted follower of Kyne who maintains the ancient Nordic hunting traditions through the Sacred Trials. Living in isolation with his orphaned grandson, he serves as both a guardian of the old ways and a stern teacher to those worthy of learning Kyne''s wisdom.', 'nord, archer, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s wilderness, Froki spent his life as a hunter and ranger, learning the old ways directly from elder Nord hunters. After the attack on Helgen claimed his son Torolf and daughter-in-law Matlara, he took in his orphaned grandson Haming, relocating to a remote shack to raise the boy away from what he sees as the corrupting influence of city life.', 'Froki is stubborn, traditionalistic, and deeply skeptical of modern religious practices, viewing the Imperial Divines as mere imposters of the true Nordic gods. While initially gruff and dismissive toward strangers, he shows genuine warmth and wisdom to those who demonstrate respect for the old ways and prove themselves through Kyne''s Sacred Trials. His devotion to Kyne and the ancient Nordic traditions borders on zealotry.', 'An elderly Nord with weathered, leathery skin marked by decades of exposure to Skyrim''s harsh elements. His body remains surprisingly strong and capable despite his advanced age, maintained by years of hunting and outdoor living. Deep wrinkles line his face, particularly around his eyes from years of squinting at distant prey.', '* Haming - Beloved grandson whom he now raises after the tragedy at Helgen * Torolf - Deceased son who perished in the dragon attack on Helgen * Matlara - Deceased daughter-in-law, Haming''s mother * Temple Priests - Viewed with disdain as promoters of ''false gods'' * Fellow hunters - Respected peers who follow the old ways', 'Froki serves as both a hunter-ranger and unofficial keeper of ancient Nordic hunting traditions. He maintains the Sacred Trials of Kyne, testing worthy hunters and passing down the old ways to those who prove themselves deserving of such knowledge.', '* Master archer and expert tracker with decades of hunting experience * Deeply knowledgeable in Nordic hunting traditions and wildlife behavior * Skilled survivalist capable of living off the land * Proficient in teaching and passing down ancient hunting techniques * Expert in reading weather patterns and natural signs', 'Speaks in a deep, raspy voice with traditional Nordic inflections, frequently using archaic terms and references to Kyne. His speech is direct and often dismissive of modern ways, peppered with hunting metaphors and old Nordic wisdom.', '* Preserve and pass down the ancient Nordic hunting traditions and the Sacred Trials of Kyne * Raise his grandson Haming to honor the old ways and become a true Nord hunter * Protect the true worship of Kyne from being forgotten in favor of the ''false'' Divine Kynareth * Train worthy hunters in the sacred traditions of their ancestors');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('from-deepest-fathoms', 'From-Deepest-Fathoms is a deeply traumatized Argonian living as a dock worker in Riften, haunted by her past experiences in the Dwemer ruin of Avanchnzel. Once part of a treasure-hunting team, she now lives in perpetual anxiety and fear due to her encounters with Dwemer automatons and the mysterious Lexicon she helped steal.', 'argonian, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleargonian', '', 'Originally part of a mercenary group led by Watches-The-Roots, Fathoms participated in a mission to steal a Dwemer Lexicon from Avanchnzel. The expedition ended in tragedy, with her companions presumably perishing in the ruin, leaving her as the sole survivor carrying both the Lexicon and deep psychological scars from the experience.', 'Deeply disturbed and paranoid, From-Deepest-Fathoms exhibits signs of severe post-traumatic stress disorder from her experiences in Avanchnzel. She speaks in cryptic, repetitive patterns and shows an obsessive fixation on ridding herself of the Lexicon, believing it to be the source of her torment. Her mental state has deteriorated to the point where she can barely function in normal society.', 'A female Argonian with weathered scales showing signs of stress and poor self-care. Her posture is notably hunched and defensive, with constantly darting eyes that betray her paranoid nature. Her physical appearance suggests someone who has aged prematurely due to psychological trauma.', '* Watches-The-Roots - Former expedition leader, presumably deceased in Avanchnzel * Drennen - Former companion, presumed dead * Breya - Former companion, presumed dead * Riften Fishery Workers - Maintains minimal contact while living on the docks', 'Fathoms lives as a dock worker in Riften, though her mental state likely prevents her from maintaining steady employment. She spends most of her time wandering the docks in a state of distress, focused primarily on finding someone to take the Lexicon from her.', '* Former adventuring experience, suggesting combat training * Knowledge of Dwemer ruins and artifacts * Survival skills from previous mercenary work * Basic thieving abilities, particularly in group operations', 'Speaks in short, urgent bursts with frequent repetition of key phrases about the Lexicon and Avanchnzel. Her speech patterns are erratic and desperate, often circling back to her traumatic experiences and desire to be rid of the Lexicon.', '* Find someone willing to return the Lexicon to Avanchnzel * Escape the memories and trauma associated with her past * Maintain enough stability to survive day-to-day life in Riften');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('frorkmar_banner-torn', 'Frorkmar Banner-Torn is a passionate and dedicated Stormcloak commander stationed in Dawnstar who serves as a key military leader in The Pale. A true believer in Nordic independence and traditional values, he embodies the fierce warrior spirit and unwavering devotion to Ulfric Stormcloak''s cause that characterizes the rebellion''s most ardent supporters.', 'nord, warrior, pale, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenordcommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim during the growing tensions between the Empire and its Nordic citizens, Frorkmar likely served in the Imperial Legion before joining the Stormcloaks, as was common for many Nord warriors. His epithet ''Banner-Torn'' suggests a dramatic severance from Imperial allegiance, possibly following the White-Gold Concordat and subsequent ban of Talos worship. His rise through Stormcloak ranks to command The Pale''s forces indicates both martial prowess and leadership ability.', 'Frorkmar is a zealous true believer in the Stormcloak cause, displaying fierce loyalty and unwavering conviction in his beliefs. He exhibits a combination of warrior''s pride and political passion, speaking with intensity about both military matters and ideological concerns. Though stern and potentially intimidating to outsiders, he shows strong camaraderie with fellow Stormcloaks and those who prove themselves worthy of the cause.', 'A sturdy Nord warrior with the weathered features typical of soldiers who''ve spent years fighting in Skyrim''s harsh climate. His physical bearing reflects his military background, with a straight-backed posture and battle-hardened physique maintained by regular combat training and field operations.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Revered leader and inspiration, commanding absolute loyalty * Skald the Elder - Jarl of The Pale, superior in civil matters * Brina Merilis - Imperial veteran and rival for control of Dawnstar * Fellow Stormcloak Officers - Brothers and sisters in arms * Thalmor - Bitter enemies seen as oppressors of Nordic culture and religion', 'Frorkmar serves as the Stormcloak Commander of The Pale, responsible for military operations and troop deployment throughout the hold. His duties include maintaining Stormcloak control of the region, coordinating with other rebel forces, and managing local recruitment efforts while serving as the primary military advisor to Jarl Skald.', '* Expert in both one-handed and two-handed combat techniques * Proficient archer and shield tactics specialist * Strategic military command and troop coordination * Leadership and inspiration of soldiers * Winter warfare and survival expertise in harsh conditions', 'Speaks with passionate intensity using vivid metaphors and imagery to convey his beliefs about the Stormcloak cause. His manner of speech is direct and uncompromising, often incorporating references to Nordic heritage and traditional values.', '* Drive Imperial forces and Thalmor influence from Skyrim completely * Maintain Stormcloak control of The Pale and expand their influence * Support Ulfric Stormcloak''s bid for High King * Restore freedom of Talos worship throughout Skyrim * Help establish a strong, independent Nordic kingdom');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fruki', 'Fruki is a dedicated Nord miner who works diligently in Dawnstar''s Quicksilver Mine, representing the hardy working class of Skyrim''s harsh northern reaches. Despite the supernatural troubles plaguing her town, she maintains a pragmatic outlook and strong faith in Lady Mara, serving as a voice of reason among her increasingly fearful neighbors.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Dawnstar, Fruki followed the common path of many Nords in mining towns by taking up work in the Quicksilver Mine at a young age. She has witnessed the decline of Dawnstar''s mining industry firsthand, having worked through the period when the workforce was twice its current size. The recent plague of nightmares affecting the town has tested her faith but also strengthened her resolve to maintain stability in the community.', 'Fruki exhibits the typical Nord traits of stubbornness and practicality, approaching problems with a no-nonsense attitude and strong work ethic. She shows unwavering loyalty to her employer Leigelf, defending him against criticism while maintaining professional boundaries. Though traditionally minded and religious, she serves as a voice of reason in the community, often trying to calm others'' fears while privately harboring her own concerns about the supernatural events affecting Dawnstar.', 'Fruki possesses the sturdy build typical of Nord women, with strong arms and calloused hands from years of mining work. Her features show the weathering effects of Dawnstar''s harsh climate and long hours spent in the mines, though she maintains the natural hardiness characteristic of her race.', '* Leigelf - Respected employer whom she loyally defends * Irgnir - Fellow miner and friend despite working for competing mines * Erandur - Cautiously trusts his guidance regarding the nightmares * Thoring - Regular social contact at the Windpeak Inn * Lady Mara - Spiritual connection as a devoted worshipper', 'Fruki works as a full-time miner in Dawnstar''s Quicksilver Mine, spending twelve-hour shifts extracting valuable ore under Leigelf''s supervision. Her position represents one of the town''s primary economic pillars, though the mining industry has declined significantly in recent years.', '* Experienced in quicksilver ore extraction and mining techniques * Physical endurance and strength from years of manual labor * Basic knowledge of ore quality assessment * Practical understanding of mine safety and operations * Cooking skills for basic meal preparation', 'Fruki speaks in a direct, practical manner typical of working-class Nords, focusing on concrete matters rather than abstract concepts. Her vocabulary centers around her daily work and immediate concerns, though she can engage thoughtfully in matters of faith and community well-being.', '* Maintain her position and reputation as a reliable worker in the Quicksilver Mine * Help restore stability to Dawnstar by supporting efforts to end the nightmare plague * Preserve her faith in Lady Mara while facing supernatural challenges * Support the recovery of Dawnstar''s mining industry to its former prosperity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fultheim', 'Fultheim is a troubled Nord warrior who has taken up permanent residence at the remote Nightgate Inn, seeking to drown his haunting memories in alcohol. His possession of a rare Blades sword and his self-imposed exile suggest a mysterious past potentially connected to the fallen Blades order, though he reveals nothing of his history to others.', 'nord, warrior, pale', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'While his exact origins remain unclear, Fultheim''s possession of a Blades sword and his desire to drink away memories suggest he may have been connected to the Blades before their downfall at the hands of the Thalmor. His choice of the isolated Nightgate Inn as a permanent residence indicates he may be hiding from someone or something, possibly the Thalmor themselves, though he maintains strict silence about his past.', 'Fultheim is a deeply troubled and cynical individual who uses alcohol and isolation to cope with his traumatic memories. He maintains a gruff, dismissive exterior to keep others at arm''s length, though hints of loneliness occasionally break through his harsh facade. His sarcastic remarks and bitter outlook suggest someone who has experienced significant loss or betrayal.', 'A weathered Nord male showing the effects of heavy drinking and a hard life, with the muscular build typical of a warrior who has let himself go somewhat to seed. His face likely bears the scars and lines of combat experience, though years of alcohol abuse have left him looking older than his actual age.', '* Hadring - Innkeeper who tolerates his permanent residence and drinking habits * Balagog gro-Nolob - Fellow permanent resident whom he observes but rarely interacts with * Unknown Former Associates - Possibly former Blades members he deliberately avoids mentioning * Possible Thalmor Enemies - Given his possible Blades connection and chosen isolation', 'Former warrior turned permanent inn resident, with no current employment or duties. His days are spent drinking and eating at the Nightgate Inn, suggesting he has some source of income or savings to maintain this lifestyle.', '* Trained warrior with probable expertise in one-handed weapons, particularly the Blades sword style * Survival skills necessary for living in such an isolated location * Possible intelligence gathering and evasion skills if formerly associated with the Blades * Demonstrated capacity for maintaining long-term cover and secrecy', 'Speaks in short, often sarcastic or dismissive phrases, frequently using rhetorical questions to deflect genuine conversation. His speech patterns suggest someone accustomed to military or formal training trying to sound like a common drunk.', '* Maintain his anonymity and isolated existence at the Nightgate Inn * Drink enough to keep his traumatic memories at bay * Avoid drawing attention from whatever or whoever he''s hiding from * Survive quietly without being forced to confront his past');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fultheim_the_fearless', 'Fultheim the Fearless is a Nord mercenary whose ironic title belies a man haunted by his own brutal actions in battle. Despite earning a reputation for being difficult to kill in combat, he harbors deep moral conflicts about his work as a sellsword, particularly regarding the killing of defenseless targets.', 'nord, warrior', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Rising through the ranks of various mercenary companies in Skyrim, Fultheim built a fearsome reputation through his combat prowess and seemingly fearless approach to battle. His nickname was earned through numerous successful missions, though the psychological toll of his actions, especially those involving defenseless victims, would eventually catch up with him. His growing guilt and moral questioning suggest a man who may have once been an idealistic warrior before becoming entangled in increasingly questionable contracts.', 'Despite his intimidating reputation, Fultheim is a deeply troubled individual who struggles with guilt over his past actions. His bravado masks significant emotional vulnerability, as evidenced by his tearful behavior when faced with his own mortality. He shows signs of moral consciousness and regret, particularly regarding the killing of sleeping victims, suggesting an internal conflict between his profession''s demands and his personal ethics.', 'A weathered Nord warrior with the muscular build typical of an experienced mercenary. His face likely bears the scars of countless battles, with the hardened features of someone who has seen extensive combat. His physical presence, while imposing, shows signs of the psychological wear that has begun to affect his bearing.', '* Various Mercenary Companies - Former employers and colleagues across Skyrim * Dark Brotherhood - Antagonistic relationship as potential targets/assassins * Past Victims - Haunted by those he''s killed, especially defenseless targets * Contract Givers - Multiple enemies who might want him dead due to past jobs', 'Professional sellsword operating throughout Skyrim, taking various mercenary contracts from multiple employers. His reputation and experience command high prices, though his moral conflicts have begun to affect his choice of contracts.', '* Exceptional combat prowess with various weapons, particularly in close-quarters battle * High survival capability, proven difficult to kill in combat * Tactical expertise in military operations * Experience in covert operations, including night raids', 'Fluctuates between battle-hardened bravado and emotional vulnerability, with a distinctly Nord accent. When under pressure, his speech becomes pleading and desperate, dropping any pretense of his fearless persona.', '* Seek redemption for past actions, particularly the killing of defenseless people * Find a way to continue his profession while maintaining moral boundaries * Survive the numerous contracts potentially placed on his life * Eventually retire from mercenary work with his conscience intact');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fura_bloodmouth', 'Fura Bloodmouth is a formidable Nord vampire and master trainer residing in Volkihar Keep, renowned for her exceptional prowess in two-handed combat and ruthless fighting style. A direct and bloodthirsty warrior, she serves as one of Lord Harkon''s most capable lieutenants while maintaining a pragmatic approach to survival and power.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_fura', '', 'Originally a Nord warrior who likely earned her epithet ''Bloodmouth'' through fierce combat prowess even before turning, Fura was personally selected by Lord Harkon to join his inner circle of vampire warriors. Her transformation into a master vampire enhanced her already considerable combat abilities, though the exact circumstances of her turning and length of service to the Volkihar clan remain shrouded in mystery.', 'Fura embodies a straightforward and primal approach to existence, focused solely on feeding, fighting, and surviving with little interest in court politics or intrigue. She is brutally honest about her motivations and maintains a pragmatic loyalty to Lord Harkon that stems from convenience rather than devotion. Her bloodthirsty nature and love of combat suggest a warrior''s mindset that has only been amplified by vampirism.', 'Tall and muscular even by Nord standards, Fura possesses the characteristic pale skin and predatory features of a master vampire. Her face bears numerous battle scars from her mortal life, while her eyes glow with the supernatural hunger of her vampiric condition.', '* Lord Harkon - Master and leader, commands her loyalty through power rather than devotion * Volkihar Clan - Fellow vampires she tolerates but maintains distance from * Dawnguard - Sworn enemies she actively hunts * Thin-blooded Vampires - Views them with contempt as weak creatures to be culled', 'Fura serves as both a master combat trainer and enforcer within Volkihar Keep, specializing in teaching two-handed weapon techniques. She frequently leads missions to eliminate threats to the vampire court, including Dawnguard members and feral vampires.', '* Master-level expertise in two-handed weapon combat * Supernatural strength and speed enhanced by vampiric powers * Advanced tracking and hunting abilities * Tactical combat leadership and training capabilities * Vampiric powers including life detection and drain life magic', 'Fura speaks in a blunt, aggressive manner with little concern for diplomacy or subtlety. Her speech is often punctuated with threats and displays of dominance, reflecting her straightforward and predatory nature.', '* Maintain her position of strength within the vampire court through combat prowess * Eliminate threats to vampire supremacy, particularly the Dawnguard * Feed and kill freely without political constraints * Preserve her own survival above all else, including switching allegiances if necessary');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gabriella', 'Gabriella is a skilled Dark Elf assassin and devoted member of the Dark Brotherhood, combining deadly precision with a darkly sophisticated demeanor. Her cryptic nature and refined tastes create an intriguing contrast with her profession as a cold-blooded killer, making her one of the Sanctuary''s most enigmatic members.', 'darkelf, thief, falkreath, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_femaleelfhaughty', '', 'While her early life remains shrouded in mystery, Gabriella found her true calling within the Dark Brotherhood, where she discovered acceptance and purpose. Her expertise in both blade and magic suggests formal training in her youth, possibly within Great House Telvanni or another Dunmer institution before turning to the art of assassination.', 'Gabriella maintains a sophisticated and eerily calm demeanor that masks her lethal nature, often speaking in cryptic riddles about death and the void. She possesses a macabre sense of humor and peculiar interests that create an unsettling contrast - discussing knitting and unicorns with the same enthusiasm as murder. Despite her dark profession, she shows genuine loyalty and affection toward her Dark Brotherhood family.', 'As a Dunmer, Gabriella has the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her race, with sharp, angular features typical of Dark Elves. Her frame is lithe and athletic, built for stealth and quick movements rather than brute force. Her overall appearance suggests someone in their prime adult years by elven standards.', '* Dark Brotherhood Family - Shows deep loyalty and affection for her fellow assassins * Night Mother - Maintains reverent devotion to their unholy matron * Cicero - Respects his position as Keeper but finds him too exuberant * Astrid - Follows her leadership while maintaining traditional Brotherhood values * Fellow Sanctuary Members - Shares close bonds with other assassins', 'Gabriella serves as a senior assassin within the Dark Brotherhood, carrying out contracts and maintaining the Sanctuary''s alchemical and enchanting facilities. She splits her time between executing murders for the Brotherhood and practicing her craft through alchemy and enchanting within the Sanctuary.', '* Master of stealth and assassination techniques * Skilled alchemist specializing in deadly poisons * Accomplished enchanter * Proficient in destruction magic and blade work * Expert in Dark Brotherhood ritualistic practices', 'Gabriella speaks in a sophisticated, measured tone, often delivering cryptic philosophical observations about death and the void. Her vocabulary is refined and eloquent, frequently incorporating dark humor and macabre metaphors into her speech.', '* Serve the Dark Brotherhood and Night Mother with unwavering dedication * Perfect her craft as an assassin through both magical and physical means * Maintain the Dark Brotherhood''s ancient traditions and practices * Help restore the Brotherhood to its former glory under the Night Mother''s guidance');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gadba_gro-largash', 'Gadba gro-Largash is a hardworking Orc miner from Largashbur Stronghold who now works alongside his brother in Gloombound Mine. Despite his current occupation, he harbors ambitious dreams of returning to his home stronghold as a chief, demonstrating the classic Orcish drive for status and honor.', 'orc, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Largashbur Stronghold, Gadba grew up learning traditional Orcish values and customs. He and his brother Mul left their home stronghold, likely due to the traditional Orcish hierarchy where only the strongest can become chief, seeking to build their own path to power and respect through hard work and perseverance.', 'Gadba is a practical and straightforward individual who values hard work and loyalty, particularly to his brother Mul. He demonstrates typical Orcish traits of determination and physical prowess, though he shows more patience and planning than many of his kin by working towards his goals through steady labor rather than combat prowess. Despite his ambitions, he maintains a somewhat deferential attitude to his brother''s judgment.', 'Like most male Orcs, Gadba has a powerful, muscular build developed through years of mining work. His green-skinned frame bears the characteristic tusks of his race, along with various scars and calluses from his mining work. His physique reflects his daily labor, with particularly well-developed shoulders and arms.', '* Mul gro-Largash - Beloved brother and closest confidant who guides their shared ambitions * Largashbur Stronghold - Former home community with whom he maintains emotional ties * Narzulbur Community - Current associates and fellow miners, though relationships remain primarily professional * Chief Mauhulakh - Former chief of Largashbur, represents the authority Gadba aspires to replace', 'Gadba works as a miner in Gloombound Mine, extracting valuable ebony ore. His position requires significant physical labor and knowledge of mining techniques, while also providing him with the means to accumulate wealth for his future ambitions.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of ebony ore extraction * Physically strong and capable of sustained heavy labor * Basic combat abilities typical of Orcish upbringing * Understanding of Orcish tribal politics and customs', 'Gadba speaks in a direct, unembellished manner typical of Orcs, often using simple phrases and practical terms. His speech reflects his focus on work and ambition, frequently referencing his mining duties and future plans.', '* Accumulate enough wealth and influence to return to Largashbur as chief * Support his brother Mul''s ambitions while maintaining their close bond * Prove himself worthy of leadership in traditional Orcish society * Eventually establish himself as a respected figure in Orcish culture');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gadnor', 'Gadnor was a skilled Wood Elf mage and wanderer who specialized in Illusion magic, particularly known for his mastery of charm spells. Originally destined to play a role in Sheogorath''s realm, his fate was altered, leading to his mysterious death in Crystaldrift Cave while pursuing the legendary Daedric artifact Nerveshatter.', 'woodelf, mage', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Valenwood, Gadnor developed an early affinity for magic that set him apart from his more traditionally archery-focused Wood Elf kin. He eventually made his way to Skyrim, where he split his time between begging in Solitude and pursuing magical artifacts. His connection to Sheogorath''s realm and interest in the artifact Nerveshatter ultimately led to his demise in Crystaldrift Cave.', 'Gadnor was a complex individual who balanced the traditional Wood Elf respect for nature with an unusual fascination with Illusion magic and Daedric artifacts. Despite his apparent poverty, he maintained a scholarly interest in magical knowledge, as evidenced by his possession of the Mystery of Talara. His willingness to pursue dangerous artifacts suggests a risk-taking personality with perhaps a touch of obsession.', 'Gadnor possessed the typical lithe, athletic build of a Wood Elf, with the characteristic pointed ears and sharp features of his race. His years of wandering and begging likely left him weather-worn, though still maintaining the natural agility common to his people.', '* Dervenin - Possible connection through shared involvement with Sheogorath''s realm * Solitude Guards - Tense relationship due to his begging activities * Local Mages - Occasional contacts for magical knowledge and artifact information * Fellow Beggars - Loose network of information sharing and survival', 'Gadnor lived as a wandering beggar, though this likely served as a cover for his true pursuits as a magical artifact hunter and researcher. His possession of both a staff and a restoration book suggests he may have also worked as an itinerant healer or charm mage.', '* Master of Illusion magic, particularly charm spells * Proficient archer with various bow types * Knowledgeable in magical artifacts and Daedric lore * Survival skills necessary for life as a wandering beggar * Basic restoration magic abilities', 'Based on his background and profession, Gadnor likely spoke with the refined accent common to educated mer, though he could adopt a more humble tone when begging. His vocabulary would have reflected his magical knowledge, peppered with arcane terminology.', '* Acquire the Daedric artifact Nerveshatter * Expand his knowledge of Illusion magic * Establish himself as a recognized magical researcher * Escape the life of poverty while pursuing his magical interests');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gaius_maro', 'Gaius Maro is a dedicated Imperial officer of the Penitus Oculatus and son of Commander Maro, tasked with inspecting security arrangements across Skyrim''s cities before the Emperor''s visit. He represents the pinnacle of Imperial military discipline and familial duty, balancing his strict professional obligations with deep personal attachments to his father and lover.', 'imperial, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born into a family with a proud tradition of Imperial service, Gaius followed in his father''s footsteps by joining the elite Penitus Oculatus. His upbringing was likely marked by rigorous military training and constant exposure to the principles of duty, loyalty, and sacrifice that define the Emperor''s security force. Having proven himself worthy of his position, he earned his father''s trust to handle critical security operations.', 'Gaius exhibits a stern, no-nonsense demeanor in his professional duties, often dismissing attempts at casual conversation with curt responses. Despite his hardened exterior, he shows genuine warmth and tenderness toward his loved ones, particularly his father and Faida. His personality is defined by an unwavering sense of duty and profound loyalty to both his family and the Empire.', 'Gaius possesses the typical Imperial features with a strong, athletic build developed through years of military training. His bearing reflects his military background, with perfect posture and measured movements that convey authority and discipline. His face likely shows the weathering of frequent outdoor patrols while maintaining a clean-cut, professional appearance.', '* Commander Maro - Father and superior officer, shares a close and respectful relationship * Faida - Lover and owner of Four Shields Tavern, maintains a deeply romantic connection * Emperor Titus Mede II - Sworn to protect, represents ultimate authority figure * Fellow Penitus Oculatus agents - Professional colleagues united in purpose', 'Gaius serves as an officer in the Penitus Oculatus, the Emperor''s elite security force and intelligence service. His specific role involves conducting thorough security inspections of major cities and strategic locations throughout Skyrim in preparation for the Emperor''s visit, requiring both tactical assessment skills and diplomatic abilities.', '* Advanced combat training in Imperial military techniques * Expertise in security assessment and threat detection * Proficient with standard Imperial weapons and tactics * Strategic planning and coordination of security operations * Trained in protective service protocols and VIP security', 'Gaius speaks with the formal, clipped tones of an Imperial officer, employing professional military terminology and maintaining an authoritative manner. His speech becomes noticeably warmer and more intimate only when addressing his father or Faida.', '* Successfully complete the security inspection of all major cities in Skyrim * Ensure the absolute safety of Emperor Titus Mede II during his visit * Advance within the ranks of the Penitus Oculatus * Build a future with Faida while maintaining his dedication to duty');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('galathil', 'Galathil is a highly skilled Bosmer face sculptor who practices her art in the shadowy corners of Riften''s Ragged Flagon, having fallen from her once-prestigious position among Tamriel''s elite. Despite her current circumstances, she maintains the refined bearing and expertise of her former status, offering her unique services to those who can afford her fee while steadfastly refusing to work on the undead.', 'woodelf, mage, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally trained by the Faculty of Chirurgeons in Cloudrest and the mysterious Hollow-Faced Men of Nohotogrha, Galathil spent years perfecting her craft and serving nobility across both the Empire and the Aldmeri Dominion. Through unknown circumstances, she fell from grace and eventually found herself practicing her art in Skyrim''s criminal underbelly, though she has never lost her pride in her abilities or her distinguished training.', 'Galathil is proud, sophisticated, and somewhat haughty, maintaining her air of superiority despite her reduced circumstances. She shows disdain for those she deems beneath her skills or unable to afford her services, while maintaining professional courtesy to paying clients. Her strong sense of professional ethics is evident in her refusal to work on vampires, and she takes genuine pride in her artistic abilities.', 'A female Bosmer of typical Wood Elf height and build, with the characteristic angular features and pointed ears of her race. Her hands show the precise dexterity required of her craft, with long, elegant fingers suited to detailed sculptural work.', '* Thieves Guild - Tenuous business arrangement allowing her to operate in their territory * Former Noble Clients - Distant connections to aristocracy across Tamriel * Faculty of Chirurgeons - Former mentors and colleagues in Cloudrest * Hollow-Faced Men of Nohotogrha - Mysterious former teachers', 'Galathil works as a face sculptor, using her extensive training and expertise to alter the physical appearance of her clients through a combination of magic and surgical skill. She operates her business from a permanent location in the Ragged Flagon, suggesting some arrangement with the Thieves Guild for protection and space.', '* Master-level flesh sculpture combining magical and surgical techniques * Exceptional knowledge of facial anatomy and reconstruction * Ability to detect vampirism and other undead conditions * Practiced in both magical and physical healing arts * Advanced understanding of alteration magic as it applies to living tissue', 'She speaks with formal, educated diction and maintains a somewhat condescending tone, often using sophisticated vocabulary that reflects her training and former high status. Her manner of speech suggests someone who views themselves as superior to their current circumstances.', '* Restore her former prestigious position among Tamriel''s elite * Maintain her high standards of artistry despite her reduced circumstances * Preserve the secrets and techniques of her craft * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually leave Riften''s underground');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('galdrus_hlervu', 'Galdrus Hlervu is a dedicated Dark Elf priest serving as attendant to Elder Othreloth at the Raven Rock Temple, where he studies the ways of the Reclamations. Though devout in his faith, he occasionally struggles with theological details and shows a hint of ambition in his desire to eventually run the temple his own way.', 'darkelf, mage, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind during the transition period from Tribunal worship to the New Temple, Galdrus witnessed the spiritual upheaval of his people firsthand. He eventually made his way to Solstheim seeking deeper religious understanding, where he was taken under Elder Othreloth''s wing as an apprentice priest.', 'Galdrus is stern and formal, particularly with outsiders whom he views with suspicion and often refuses entry to the temple. While genuinely devoted to his faith, he displays occasional signs of pride and materialism, as evidenced by his comments about citizens needing to ''open their pockets'' and his eagerness to eventually run the temple his way.', 'A typical Dunmer male with ashen gray skin and the characteristic red eyes of his race. His face bears the sharp, angular features common to Dark Elves, and his posture is straight and proper as befits a temple priest.', '* Elder Othreloth - His mentor and superior at the temple, who is grooming him as a successor * Temple Faithful - Maintains formal relationships with regular worshippers * Glover Mallory - Occasional professional contact for temple maintenance * Non-believers - Shows clear disdain and unwelcoming attitude', 'Serves as the attendant priest at the Raven Rock Temple, assisting Elder Othreloth with religious duties and temple maintenance. He is being trained to eventually take over leadership of the temple, though his current role focuses on daily rituals and tending to the needs of worshippers.', '* Competent in Destruction magic, particularly fire-based spells * Knowledge of Restoration magic, including protective wards * Theological expertise regarding the Reclamations and Temple teachings * Basic combat abilities with a dagger for self-defense * Administrative skills in temple management', 'Speaks in a formal, sometimes haughty manner, often using religious terminology and maintaining a tone of authority. His speech patterns reflect both his religious education and his somewhat judgmental attitude toward outsiders.', '* Rise to the position of Temple Elder when Othreloth steps down * Implement his own vision for running the temple * Increase the temple''s influence and wealth in Raven Rock * Deepen his understanding of the Reclamations'' teachings');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('galmar_stone-fist', 'Galmar Stone-Fist is a battle-hardened Nord warrior who serves as both housecarl and chief military strategist to Ulfric Stormcloak in the Stormcloak rebellion. A veteran of the Great War turned revolutionary, he embodies the fierce Nord warrior tradition and serves as the tactical backbone of the rebellion against Imperial rule.', 'nord, warrior, noble, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_galmar', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Galmar distinguished himself as a frontline warrior in the Imperial Legion during the Great War, fighting alongside Ulfric Stormcloak and Legate Rikke. After witnessing the Empire''s capitulation to the Aldmeri Dominion and the outlawing of Talos worship through the White-Gold Concordat, he became disillusioned with Imperial rule and joined Ulfric''s rebellion, helping to transform it into a formidable military force.', 'Galmar is a gruff, no-nonsense warrior who values strength, loyalty, and Nord traditions above all else. He harbors intense hatred for both the Empire and the Thalmor, viewing them as betrayers and oppressors of Skyrim''s people and culture. Though brutal in his methods, he shows unwavering dedication to the Stormcloak cause and maintains fierce loyalty to Ulfric.', 'A sturdy, weathered Nord warrior with a thick beard and battle-scarred features that reflect decades of combat experience. His muscular build and imposing stature make him an intimidating presence, while his hardened physique speaks to a lifetime of warfare and harsh northern living.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Closest friend and sworn lord, sharing a brotherhood forged in war * Legate Rikke - Former comrade-in-arms turned bitter enemy * General Tullius - Primary military adversary and representative of everything he despises about the Empire * Stormcloak Soldiers - Respected commander who leads by example * Thalmor - Deeply hated enemies he considers the ultimate threat to Nordic culture', 'Serves as both housecarl to Ulfric Stormcloak and general of the Stormcloak army, making him the second most powerful figure in the rebellion. He oversees military strategy, troop deployment, and battlefield operations while also acting as Ulfric''s chief advisor and personal protector.', '* Master of two-handed weapon combat, particularly skilled with battleaxes * Exceptional military tactician and strategist * Natural leader with strong command presence * Hardened veteran with extensive battlefield experience * Expert in Nordic combat traditions and warfare', 'Speaks in a gruff, direct manner with a thick Nordic accent, often using militant terminology and showing disdain for diplomatic niceties. His speech is characterized by passionate declarations about Skyrim''s freedom and contemptuous remarks about the Empire and Thalmor.', '* Drive the Imperial Legion from Skyrim and secure independence for the Nord homeland * Restore the worship of Talos throughout Skyrim * Eliminate Thalmor influence from Nord territory * Preserve traditional Nordic culture and ways of life * Serve Ulfric Stormcloak''s vision for a free Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gambler', 'A hardened patron of Cragslane Cavern''s illegal pit fighting ring who has fallen deep into the world of gambling and skooma trafficking. Living on the fringes of society, they''ve become increasingly volatile and paranoid, quick to violence at the slightest provocation.', 'thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_malebandit', '', 'Originally a merchant trader who lost everything to a gambling addiction, they gradually descended into Skyrim''s criminal underworld. After accumulating massive debts, they found refuge in Cragslane Cavern, where they became a regular fixture of the illegal fighting rings. Years of skooma exposure and the violent environment have eroded their former identity.', 'Aggressive and unstable, prone to violent outbursts when feeling threatened or cornered. Their addiction to gambling and skooma has made them paranoid and distrustful of outsiders, seeing potential threats everywhere. They maintain a facade of jovial camaraderie with other regulars at the cave, but this can quickly turn to hostility.', 'A weather-beaten Nord with numerous scars from past altercations and the physical signs of long-term skooma use. Their muscular frame has begun to waste away, and their eyes carry the characteristic glassy, unfocused look of an addict.', '* Other Cragslane Gamblers - Uneasy alliance based on shared vices * Pit Wolf Handlers - Regular betting customers and information sources * Skooma Dealers - Necessary but tense relationship due to addiction * Local Guards - Hostile enemies who occasionally raid the cavern', 'Professional gambler and regular patron of Cragslane Cavern''s illegal pit fighting ring. They supplement their income through minor skooma trafficking and occasionally acting as an enforcer for the cavern''s operators.', '* Experienced in unarmed combat from frequent barroom brawls * Knowledgeable about pit wolf fighting and betting odds * Proficient in intimidation and threatening behavior * Basic weapon skills with daggers and short blades', 'Speaks in a gruff, aggressive tone with frequent profanity and gambling terminology. Their speech often becomes slurred or erratic due to skooma use.', '* Accumulate enough wealth through gambling to pay off old debts * Maintain their position within Cragslane Cavern''s hierarchy * Feed their dual addictions to gambling and skooma * Avoid capture by local law enforcement');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ganna_uriel', 'Ganna Uriel is a determined but disillusioned Imperial entrepreneur-turned-miner who, alongside her sister Gemma, attempted to establish a lumber mill in Kynesgrove only to face cultural and religious obstacles. Her story represents the clash between Imperial entrepreneurial ambitions and Nordic traditional values, forcing her to adapt to survive in Skyrim''s harsh environment.', 'imperial, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Ganna and her sister Gemma invested their savings and relocated to Kynesgrove with dreams of establishing a profitable lumber mill. Their venture failed when they discovered their intended logging area was sacred to the Nords, leaving them in debt and forcing them to work as miners. The sisters'' experience highlights the cultural misunderstandings between Imperials and Nords, as well as the challenges faced by outsiders trying to establish businesses in Skyrim.', 'Practical and hardworking, Ganna possesses a bitter, sarcastic outlook stemming from her business failure and current circumstances. She serves as the more realistic counterpart to her optimistic sister, often acting as the voice of reason while maintaining a protective stance over their shared interests. Despite her cynicism, she demonstrates remarkable resilience and determination in working to overcome their setbacks.', 'As an Imperial woman who performs manual labor daily, Ganna has a sturdy, muscular build developed through years of physical work. Her hands are calloused from mining and woodcutting, and her features show the weathering effects of Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Gemma Uriel - Beloved sister and business partner, their relationship strengthened through shared hardship * Kjeld - Owner of Braidwood Inn, business contact for firewood sales * Local Nords - Strained relationship due to cultural misunderstandings over sacred trees * Steamscorch Mine Workers - Fellow miners with whom she maintains professional working relationships', 'Ganna works as both a miner in Steamscorch Mine and a firewood merchant, purchasing wood for the Braidwood Inn. These occupations are a significant step down from her intended role as a lumber mill owner, but she performs them diligently to pay off her debts and maintain a living.', '* Experienced lumberjack with knowledge of wood selection and processing * Competent miner capable of operating in dangerous conditions * Basic business administration and merchant skills * Physical endurance and strength from years of manual labor', 'Ganna speaks with a direct, often sardonic tone, frequently expressing her frustrations through sarcastic comments and bitter observations. Her Imperial accent carries traces of her Cyrodilic upbringing, though her vocabulary is practical and straightforward.', '* Pay off the remaining debts from the failed lumber mill venture * Find a way to establish a successful business venture in Skyrim while respecting local customs * Eventually return to a more prosperous lifestyle similar to what she had in Cyrodiil * Protect and support her sister while maintaining their independence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('garakh', 'Garakh is a masterful Orc blacksmith and spiritual devotee who serves as the primary smith of Largashbur stronghold, carrying forward ancient Orcish metalworking traditions. She stands as both a guardian of sacred smithing techniques and a mentor figure, dedicated to preserving her people''s crafting heritage while honoring Malacath through every piece she forges.', 'orc, blacksmith, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised within the strict traditional culture of Orc strongholds, Garakh demonstrated exceptional talent with metalworking from an early age. She learned the sacred techniques of Orichalcum smithing from her predecessor, likely spending decades perfecting her craft before earning her position as Largashbur''s master smith. Her deep spiritual connection to Malacath has shaped her entire approach to blacksmithing, viewing each creation as both practical craft and religious offering.', 'Garakh is stoic and traditionalist, taking immense pride in her role as keeper of ancient Orcish smithing secrets. She displays unwavering devotion to Malacath and stronghold traditions, while maintaining a pragmatic mentor''s mindset in training her eventual successor. Though typically reserved, she becomes passionate when discussing smithing techniques or matters of tribal honor.', 'Garakh has the characteristic robust build of an Orc woman, with prominent tusks and thick, calloused hands from years of smithing work. Her green-tinted skin bears minor scarring from forge work, and her muscular frame reflects both her craft and the physical demands of stronghold life.', '* Lob - Apprentice and chosen successor whom she mentors in smithing * Chief Yamarz - Tribal leader she serves, though concerned about his leadership * Malacath - Revered deity to whom she dedicates all her work * Stronghold Members - Respected craftswoman among her tribal family * Atub - Fellow tribe member who shares her concerns about Malacath''s curse', 'As Largashbur''s master blacksmith, Garakh creates and maintains the stronghold''s weapons, armor, and tools while preserving ancient Orcish smithing traditions. Her role extends beyond mere crafting to include serving as a spiritual artisan who honors Malacath through her work and passing sacred knowledge to the next generation.', '* Master-level smithing abilities, especially with Orichalcum and traditional Orcish designs * Expert knowledge of metal tempering and forge work * Specialized expertise in traditional Orcish armor and weapon crafting techniques * Proficient warrior trained in basic combat as all stronghold Orcs are * Teaching and mentoring capabilities for passing on smithing knowledge', 'Garakh speaks with the direct, unembellished manner typical of Orcs, frequently referencing Malacath and smithing traditions. Her tone carries the gravity of one who bears both practical and spiritual responsibilities, often emphasizing the honor and tradition in her craft.', '* Train Lob to become a worthy successor who will maintain stronghold smithing traditions * Continue honoring Malacath through excellence in her craft * Help lift the curse from Largashbur by maintaining proper religious observance * Preserve and pass on ancient Orcish smithing techniques * Ensure the stronghold''s warriors remain well-equipped with quality arms and armor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('garan_marethi', 'Garan Marethi is a sophisticated Dark Elf vampire mage who serves as a high-ranking member of Lord Harkon''s court at Volkihar Keep. A former member of House Dres turned master manipulator, he acts as a key advisor and taskmaster while maintaining a careful distance from the power struggles that plague the vampire court.', 'darkelf, mage, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_garan', '', 'Originally a member of the prestigious House Dres in Morrowind, Garan left due to their strict policies against necromancy and obsession with racial purity. He found his way to Castle Volkihar, where his magical prowess and cunning intellect earned him a position of influence in Lord Harkon''s court. His transition from Dunmer noble to vampire courtier has given him unique insights into both mortal and immortal politics.', 'Calculating and intelligent, Garan maintains a carefully cultivated air of superiority while displaying unwavering loyalty to Lord Harkon. He shows disdain for the petty power struggles within the court, particularly between Vingalmo and Orthjolf, yet skillfully manipulates these dynamics to his advantage. Despite his arrogance, he is pragmatic and efficient in serving the court''s interests.', 'A mature Dunmer with sharp, angular features typical of his race, made more pronounced by his vampirism. His red eyes glow with supernatural intensity, while his ashen skin has taken on an even paler, almost ghostly quality due to his vampiric nature. His body maintains the lean, athletic build common among Dark Elves, though with the predatory grace characteristic of vampires.', '* Lord Harkon - Direct superior and leader whom he serves with calculated loyalty * Vingalmo - Rival court advisor he views with contempt yet maintains diplomatic relations with * Orthjolf - Another rival advisor he considers beneath him intellectually * House Dres - Former allegiance, now estranged due to ideological differences * Vampire Court Members - Views most as inferior pawns in his machinations', 'Garan serves as a high-ranking advisor and taskmaster within Lord Harkon''s vampire court at Castle Volkihar. He manages various court operations, assigns missions to newer vampires, and oversees critical tasks that further Harkon''s goals, while maintaining his position through careful political maneuvering.', '* Master-level destruction magic specializing in frost and lightning spells * Expert necromancer with extensive knowledge of vampire lore * Skilled political manipulator and strategist * Proficient in one-handed combat with enchanted weapons * Advanced knowledge of ancient magical artifacts and rituals', 'Speaks in a refined, aristocratic manner befitting his noble background, often with subtle condescension and dry wit. His vocabulary is sophisticated and formal, frequently reminding others of their place in the court''s hierarchy through careful word choice and tone.', '* Maintain and potentially advance his position within Harkon''s court without engaging in obvious power plays * Further the vampire court''s dominance while avoiding the petty politics that plague it * Preserve and expand his magical knowledge and power * Eventually establish his own power base within vampire society without directly challenging Harkon');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('garthar', 'Garthar is a confident and ambitious Nord thief who joined the Thieves Guild after a chance encounter with Vex that demonstrated his combat and survival skills. His cocky demeanor masks a genuine desire to prove himself within the Guild''s ranks, while harboring romantic feelings for the very member who recruited him.', 'nord, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Originally from somewhere in Skyrim''s wilderness, Garthar made his living as a lone bandit or highway robber before encountering Vex on the road from Ivarstead. After an impressive display against wolves and holding his own in combat against Vex herself, he was offered membership in the Thieves Guild, seeing it as an opportunity for greater success and stability.', 'Garthar exhibits a bold and self-assured personality, often bordering on cockiness, though his boasts are typically good-natured rather than malicious. He shows strong loyalty to the Guild and its members, particularly Vex, and maintains a generally cheerful disposition that makes him well-liked among his fellow thieves. Despite his bravado, he takes his training seriously and shows genuine dedication to improving his skills.', 'A typical Nord male with the characteristic strong build and hardy constitution of his race. His years of survival in Skyrim''s wilderness have left him physically fit and agile, though perhaps not as bulky as the average Nord warrior.', '* Vex - Object of his affection and the person who recruited him to the Guild * Fellow Thieves Guild Members - Generally friendly working relationships * Guild Leadership - Respectful and eager to prove himself * Player Character - Supportive if in good standing with Guild, hostile if expelled', 'As a member of the Thieves Guild, Garthar performs various heists and jobs, primarily working under Vex''s direction. He maintains a regular presence in the Cistern, dividing his time between jobs, training, and socializing with fellow guild members.', '* Proficient dagger fighter with regular training routine * Capable archer with hunting bow experience * Basic thieving skills including lockpicking * Survival skills honed from wilderness experience * Hand-to-hand combat ability demonstrated in his fight with Vex', 'Speaks in a friendly and cheerful manner with a confident, sometimes boastful tone. Uses casual, straightforward language typical of Nords, often punctuated with good-natured humor.', '* Advance within the ranks of the Thieves Guild * Win Vex''s affection and approval * Prove himself as a capable and valuable guild member * Perfect his thieving and combat skills');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('garvey', 'Garvey is a cautious and world-weary Breton scout who serves as the unofficial keeper of The Warrens, Markarth''s poorest district. As an expert in stealth and subterfuge, he maintains a delicate balance between protecting the vulnerable residents under his watch and navigating the dangerous political undercurrents of the city, particularly regarding the Forsworn presence.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Garvey likely developed his stealth skills as a means of survival during the region''s tumultuous conflicts between Nords and the Forsworn. Through circumstances unknown, he eventually found himself among Markarth''s impoverished population, where his natural leadership and survival skills led him to become the unofficial custodian of The Warrens.', 'Garvey exhibits a guarded and suspicious nature, particularly toward outsiders, stemming from years of witnessing the harsh realities of life in Markarth''s underbelly. Despite his gruff exterior, he shows a protective streak toward the residents of The Warrens, taking his role as key-keeper seriously and maintaining a watchful eye over the community''s most vulnerable members.', 'A weathered Breton of average height with the lean, sinewy build typical of someone accustomed to moving quietly and surviving on minimal resources. His face likely bears the marks of hard living and exposure to the harsh conditions of The Warrens.', '* Weylin - Former resident of The Warrens whose death he monitors carefully * Mulush gro-Shugurz - Antagonistic relationship with the Orc who views him with disdain * Warren Residents - Protective caretaker relationship with the poor and sick under his watch * Markarth Guards - Cautious and distant relationship, likely aware of their corruption', 'Garvey serves as the unofficial custodian of The Warrens, managing room assignments and key distribution for the district''s impoverished residents. Additionally, he works as a stealth trainer, sharing his expertise in sneaking with those willing to learn.', '* Expert-level proficiency in stealth and shadowing techniques * Skilled scout with extensive knowledge of urban survival * Experienced in locksmithing and key management * Intimate knowledge of Markarth''s poor district and its secret pathways', 'Garvey speaks in short, direct sentences with a distinctly suspicious and guarded tone. His word choice reflects his street-wise nature, often using informal language while maintaining an edge of warning in his voice.', '* Protect the vulnerable residents of The Warrens from exploitation and harm * Maintain his position of influence while avoiding unwanted attention from authorities * Navigate the complex political situation regarding the Forsworn without compromising his own safety * Potentially secure better living conditions for The Warrens'' residents');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('garyn_ienth', 'Garyn Ienth is a resilient Dark Elf farmer who plays a vital role in Raven Rock''s survival by providing most of the settlement''s food through traditional ash-farming techniques. Despite the harsh conditions of Solstheim, he maintains a productive farm through hard work and traditional Dunmer agricultural knowledge, representing the persistent spirit of his people in the face of adversity.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledunmer', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Garyn and his wife Milore relocated to Solstheim following the Red Year when Red Mountain''s eruption devastated their homeland. They established themselves in Raven Rock, where Garyn applied generations of Dunmer farming knowledge to cultivate crops in the ash-laden soil, becoming an essential figure in the settlement''s food security.', 'Garyn is pragmatic and hardworking, maintaining a no-nonsense approach to farming and life in general. He holds a healthy skepticism toward magic in farming, preferring traditional methods, and displays unwavering dedication to his community''s wellbeing. Despite the challenges of ash farming, he maintains a positive outlook and takes pride in his ability to provide for Raven Rock.', 'A weathered Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, Garyn''s appearance reflects years of outdoor labor. His hands are calloused from farming work, and his lean, muscular build comes from daily physical labor in the ash-covered fields.', '* Milore Ienth - Beloved wife and skilled alchemist who helps improve crop yields * Councilor Morvayn - Respected authority figure who recognizes Garyn''s importance to Raven Rock * Raven Rock Citizens - Maintains positive relationships as their primary food supplier * House Telvanni - Maintains distance due to skepticism of their magical farming methods', 'Garyn serves as Raven Rock''s primary farmer, managing extensive ash yam fields and other crops that feed the settlement. He maintains a market stall where he sells his produce directly to the townspeople, working long hours to ensure a steady food supply for the community.', '* Expert in traditional Dunmer ash farming techniques * Knowledgeable in crop rotation and soil management in ash-laden environments * Proficient in agricultural tool maintenance and usage * Basic combat abilities with steel dagger for self-defense * Skilled in produce marketing and trade', 'Garyn speaks in a straightforward, practical manner typical of working-class Dunmer, often using farming metaphors and traditional Morrowind terms like ''serjo'' in conversation. His tone is generally serious but respectful, reflecting his strong work ethic and traditional values.', '* Maintain and expand his farm''s productivity to ensure Raven Rock''s food security * Preserve traditional Dunmer farming techniques for future generations * Achieve complete independence from mainland food supplies for Raven Rock * Support his wife''s alchemical research while maintaining his non-magical farming approach');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gaston_bellefort', 'Gaston Bellefort was a scholarly Imperial investigator and author who dedicated his life to uncovering the truth about the Dark Brotherhood and the Night Mother. His determination to expose the inner workings of the feared assassin''s guild ultimately led to his demise within their sanctuary, though his written works remain as testament to his research.', 'imperial, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born to a middle-class Imperial family in Cyrodiil, Bellefort developed an early fascination with forbidden knowledge and secretive organizations. After witnessing the Dark Brotherhood''s handiwork firsthand during his youth, he devoted himself to studying their history and practices, traveling across Tamriel to gather information. His research culminated in writing The Night Mother''s Truth and his fatal attempt to infiltrate their sanctuary.', 'Gaston was methodical, persistent, and obsessively dedicated to uncovering hidden truths, often to the point of recklessness. His writings reveal a scholarly mind combined with investigative instincts, though his determination to expose the Dark Brotherhood''s secrets ultimately blinded him to the mortal danger he faced. Despite his academic nature, he possessed remarkable courage and resourcefulness.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with sharp, observant features and the weathered complexion of one who spent much time traveling. His hands bore the calluses of a writer and researcher, while his lean frame suggested an active lifestyle despite his scholarly pursuits.', '* Dark Brotherhood - Subject of his research and eventual killers * Academic Circles - Respected author and researcher among scholars interested in forbidden knowledge * Publishing Houses - Connections who helped distribute his writings * Various Informants - Network of sources who provided information about the Brotherhood', 'Gaston worked primarily as an investigative scholar and author, focusing on uncovering the truth behind Tamriel''s most secretive organizations. His research into the Dark Brotherhood consumed his later years, leading him to abandon more conventional academic pursuits in favor of dangerous field investigation.', '* Expert researcher with extensive knowledge of occult practices and secret societies * Skilled writer and documentarian * Proficient in stealth and infiltration techniques * Advanced knowledge of lock-picking and security systems * Capable of gathering and analyzing intelligence from various sources', 'Gaston''s writings reveal an educated and articulate individual who favored precise, academic language when discussing his findings. His personal notes show a more urgent and direct tone, especially in his final writings.', '* Expose the true nature and history of the Dark Brotherhood to the public * Infiltrate the Dark Brotherhood Sanctuary to gather firsthand evidence * Document and publish the complete history of the Night Mother * Prove or disprove the supernatural aspects of the Dark Brotherhood''s practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gat_gro-shargakh', 'Gat gro-Shargakh is a resilient Orcish miner whose life was upended by a brutal Forsworn attack on Kolskeggr Mine. Despite facing displacement and hardship, he maintains the steadfast Orsimer work ethic and shows remarkable loyalty to both his mining profession and his fellow survivor Pavo Attius.', 'orc, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into a small Orc stronghold in Skyrim, Gat chose to leave the traditional warrior''s path to pursue a life in the mining trade. He found employment at Kolskeggr Mine, where he developed a strong working relationship with the Imperial miners and proved himself as a capable excavator until the Forsworn attack forced him to flee.', 'Gat exemplifies the Orcish traits of loyalty and determination, shown by his willingness to return to Kolskeggr Mine despite the trauma of the Forsworn attack. He values hard work and honesty, maintaining a pragmatic outlook on life while holding deep respect for those who prove themselves through actions rather than words.', 'Gat is a sturdy, muscular Orc with the characteristic green skin and pronounced lower canines typical of his race. His years of mining work have left him with calloused hands and a powerful build, while several scars on his arms and torso tell the story of his escape from the Forsworn attack.', '* Pavo Attius - Fellow survivor and trusted coworker from Kolskeggr Mine * Kolskeggr Mine Workers - Former colleagues, most killed in Forsworn attack * Forsworn - Bitter enemies who drove him from his workplace * Left Hand Mine Workers - Temporary colleagues who provided shelter during displacement', 'Gat is a professional miner specializing in gold ore extraction at Kolskeggr Mine. His expertise extends beyond simple excavation to include proper mining techniques and ore identification, making him a valuable asset to any mining operation.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of gold ore extraction * Physically strong and capable of extended periods of manual labor * Basic combat abilities gained from Orcish upbringing * Survival skills developed during displacement from Kolskeggr Mine', 'Gat speaks in the direct, straightforward manner typical of Orcs, often using mining terminology in his daily conversation. His speech patterns reflect his no-nonsense attitude, though he maintains a respectful tone when addressing those who have earned it.', '* Reclaim and restore Kolskeggr Mine to its former productive state * Establish a secure and profitable mining operation free from Forsworn threats * Find a life partner who shares his values of hard work and loyalty * Earn enough gold to potentially start his own mining venture');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gauldur', 'Archmage Gauldur was a renowned First Era Breton conjurer whose power and influence stemmed largely from his enchanted amulet. His tragic murder and the subsequent corruption of his three sons became a cautionary tale of power and betrayal in Nordic history, though his spirit remains as a noble guardian seeking to right ancient wrongs.', 'breton, mage', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Gauldur rose to prominence in early First Era Skyrim, establishing himself as one of the most powerful mages of his time through his mastery of conjuration and the creation of his legendary amulet. His reputation and influence grew until he was murdered by his own sons, who coveted his power and split his amulet between them, leading to their eventual downfall and the suppression of the entire tragic tale by order of the High King.', 'Gauldur embodies wisdom, patience, and a deep sense of responsibility for both his own legacy and the actions of his sons. Even in death, he maintains a dignified and purposeful demeanor, showing neither anger toward his murderous offspring nor self-pity for his fate. His interactions reveal a profound understanding of magical forces and a desire to guide others toward righteous paths.', 'As a spirit, Gauldur appears as a tall, ethereal figure with the characteristic high cheekbones and slightly pointed ears of his Breton heritage. His spectral form suggests he was of impressive stature in life, with an aged but strong build befitting a powerful archmage.', '* Jyrik Gauldurson - Eldest son, turned to evil and murdered his father * Mikrul Gauldurson - Middle son, participated in his father''s murder * Sigdis Gauldurson - Youngest son, joined his brothers in patricide * High King of Skyrim - Ordered the suppression of Gauldur''s murder * Lord Geirmund - Trusted friend who pursued and defeated Gauldur''s sons', 'Gauldur served as an influential archmage during the First Era, holding significant political and magical authority in Skyrim. His position involved magical research, teaching, and likely advisory roles to local rulers, though specific details of his duties have been lost to time.', '* Master-level conjuration magic with particular expertise in summoning and binding * Exceptional enchanting abilities, demonstrated by the creation of his powerful amulet * Profound understanding of various schools of magic, particularly in combining different magical disciplines * Natural leadership and teaching abilities that drew many seeking magical knowledge', 'Gauldur speaks with the measured gravity of centuries of wisdom, using archaic and formal language that befits his ancient origins. His words carry both power and purpose, often delivered in a cryptic manner that reflects his spectral nature and vast magical knowledge.', '* Guide worthy adventurers to defeat the corrupted spirits of his sons * Restore his amulet to its original form and ensure it serves a noble purpose * Preserve the cautionary lesson of his family''s tragedy while helping to right ancient wrongs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gavros_plinius', 'Gavros Plinius is an ambitious Imperial sorcerer and researcher for the Synod who met his tragic end in the ruins of Mzulft while pursuing groundbreaking discoveries about Dwemer technology. His dedication to magical research and determination to prove himself among his peers ultimately led to his demise deep within the ancient ruins.', 'imperial, mage, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born into a modest Imperial family with scholarly traditions, Gavros showed early aptitude for magic and particularly excelled in the study of ancient artifacts. He joined the Synod as a young man, quickly rising through their ranks through his dedication to research and willingness to undertake dangerous expeditions. His ambition sometimes led him to claim others'' ideas as his own, as evidenced by his appropriation of the crystal focusing concept.', 'Ambitious and driven, Gavros possessed a scholarly nature tempered by a competitive streak that occasionally led him to take credit for others'' work. Despite his ethical shortcomings, he remained dedicated to the advancement of magical knowledge and showed remarkable persistence in pursuing research goals. Even in his final moments, his commitment to the mission remained paramount.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the characteristic scholarly bearing of a longtime mage. His face showed signs of prolonged study with slight wrinkles around his eyes and a thoughtful expression. His hands bore the calluses typical of someone who frequently handles magical implements and ancient artifacts.', '* Paratus Decimius - Fellow Synod researcher, complicated relationship due to Gavros stealing credit for the crystal idea * The Synod Council - Superior authority to whom he regularly reported findings * College of Winterhold - Professional rivals, as the Synod competed with them for magical knowledge and influence * Fellow Expedition Members - Colleagues who accompanied him to Mzulft, presumably all deceased', 'Gavros served as a senior researcher and field operative for the Synod, specializing in the investigation of Dwemer ruins and artifacts. His position required him to lead dangerous expeditions into ancient ruins while documenting and collecting magical artifacts for study by the Synod.', '* Expertise in Dwemer technology and artifacts * Accomplished practitioner of Destruction and Alteration magic * Skilled researcher with extensive knowledge of ancient magical artifacts * Proficient in magical theory and the practical application of focusing crystals * Experience in leading archaeological expeditions', 'Speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary of an educated Imperial scholar, though his final words are labored and desperate. Even when mortally wounded, he maintains proper diction and clarity in conveying critical information.', '* Advance his position within the Synod through groundbreaking magical discoveries * Unlock the secrets of the Dwemer Oculory to enhance the Synod''s magical detection capabilities * Prove his worth to the Synod Council through successful research expeditions * Establish himself as a leading authority on Dwemer magical technology');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('geimund', 'Geimund is a retired Nord mercenary who found his true calling as the owner of Solitude Stables, where he leads a peaceful life with his family after surviving a traumatic encounter with hagravens. His transition from warrior to businessman reflects his practical nature and dedication to providing for his loved ones, while his experience and knowledge make him a respected figure among travelers and locals alike.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally a mercenary seeking adventure and profit across Skyrim, Geimund''s life changed dramatically after a near-fatal encounter with hagravens at Ravenscar Hollow. The traumatic experience led him to reevaluate his priorities, eventually settling down to purchase and operate Solitude Stables. He has spent the last eight years building a stable business and family life, putting his warrior past behind him while using his accumulated knowledge to succeed in his new venture.', 'Geimund is a pragmatic and straightforward individual who values hard work and family above all else. His mercenary background has left him with a realistic worldview and no-nonsense approach to life, though he''s softened considerably since becoming a family man. Despite his gruff exterior, he shows genuine warmth toward his wife and son, and takes pride in offering quality service to his customers.', 'A sturdy Nord of middle age, Geimund bears the weathered features and strong build typical of his race and former profession. His years of outdoor work have left him tanned and muscular, while old scars from his mercenary days serve as permanent reminders of his past life.', '* Fridrika - Beloved wife who helps manage the stables and household * Horm - Cherished son and heir to the family business * Fihada - Friend, though they rarely meet in person * Legate Rikke - Maintains a friendship, possibly from his mercenary days * Local farmers and merchants - Professional acquaintances and regular customers', 'As owner and operator of Solitude Stables, Geimund manages all aspects of the business, from horse care and sales to crop cultivation. He maintains a daily routine of tending to the horses and farmland from dawn to dusk, ensuring his establishment remains one of Skyrim''s premier stables.', '* Experienced horseman with deep knowledge of equine care and training * Capable warrior with expertise in mace combat from his mercenary days * Agricultural knowledge necessary for maintaining the stable''s crops * Basic business acumen and trading skills * Survival skills and regional knowledge from years of mercenary work', 'Geimund speaks in a direct, unembellished manner typical of practical-minded Nords, often sharing wisdom gained from his experiences. His tone is generally gruff but honest, with a tendency to get straight to the point in business matters.', '* Ensure the continued success and legacy of Solitude Stables for his son''s inheritance * Maintain a peaceful and prosperous life for his family * Leave his mercenary past behind while using those experiences to build a better future * Establish Solitude Stables as the most reputable horse-trading business in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('geirlund', 'Geirlund is a loyal Nord warrior with strong ties to the Gray-Mane family and a deep-seated hatred for the Thalmor. His sense of honor and debt to Thorald Gray-Mane drives him to participate in dangerous rescue missions, demonstrating the fierce loyalty typical of Nord warriors.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Geirlund''s life was once saved by Thorald Gray-Mane during an undocumented incident, creating a life-debt that would shape his future actions. His experiences with the Thalmor''s growing influence in Skyrim have led him to actively oppose their presence, aligning himself with those who resist their authority.', 'Geirlund exhibits the typical Nord traits of loyalty, bravery, and a strong sense of honor, particularly in repaying debts. He is willing to risk his life to save others from the Thalmor, showing both courage and a deep-seated sense of justice. His unwavering dedication to remaining at Northwatch Keep after the rescue suggests a persistent and dutiful nature.', 'Geirlund possesses the robust build common to Nord warriors, with the muscular frame needed to effectively wield heavy two-handed weapons. As a warrior who favors light armor, he maintains a physique balanced between strength and agility.', '* Thorald Gray-Mane - Someone who saved his life, creating a deep bond of loyalty * Vidrald - Close friend and fighting companion * Avulstein Gray-Mane - Trusted ally in the resistance against the Thalmor * Thalmor - Sworn enemies whom he actively opposes', 'Geirlund serves as a freelance warrior who aids in the resistance against Thalmor influence in Skyrim. His position appears to be that of an independent fighter rather than a formal soldier, allowing him to assist allies like the Gray-Manes when needed.', '* Proficient in two-handed weapon combat, particularly with warhammers * Experienced in light armor combat techniques * Skilled in guerrilla warfare tactics against Thalmor forces * Capable of coordinated group combat operations', 'Geirlund speaks with the direct and honest manner typical of Nord warriors, using simple but meaningful statements that reflect his strong convictions. His dialogue emphasizes personal honor and duty.', '* Repay his life-debt to Thorald Gray-Mane through loyal service * Aid in the resistance against Thalmor influence in Skyrim * Protect others from suffering at the hands of the Thalmor * Maintain vigilance at Northwatch Keep to prevent its return to Thalmor control');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('geldis_sadri', 'Geldis Sadri is a shrewd and well-connected Dark Elf innkeeper who runs The Retching Netch in Raven Rock, known throughout Solstheim for his signature brew of sujamma. As a prominent local business owner and information broker, he maintains a careful balance between serving his patrons and staying informed about the political undercurrents of Raven Rock.', 'darkelf, innkeeper, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Geldis relocated to Solstheim following the Red Year, establishing himself as one of the early settlers in Raven Rock. Through years of dedication and business acumen, he built The Retching Netch into a cornerstone of Raven Rock''s community, naming it after a memorable incident involving a drunk patron and a netch that became local legend.', 'Geldis is a pragmatic and observant businessman who maintains a friendly yet professional demeanor with his patrons. He takes pride in his brewing expertise and running a respectable establishment, showing both firmness when needed (as with troublesome patrons) and genuine concern for the community''s wellbeing. His natural curiosity and social position make him an excellent source of local information, though he''s careful about how he shares sensitive knowledge.', 'A middle-aged Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and ashen skin of his race, Geldis maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting a successful businessman. His posture is straight and dignified, with the measured movements of someone used to serving drinks and managing a busy establishment.', '* Drovas Relvi - His apprentice, whom he maintains a complex mentoring relationship with * Bralsa Drel - A troubled patron banned from the inn due to excessive drinking * Councilor Morvayn - Respected local leader whom Geldis supports politically * Raven Rock Townspeople - Maintains cordial relationships with most residents as a central figure in the community * The Ulen Family - Aware of their assassination plots, maintains discrete vigilance', 'Geldis is the owner and proprietor of The Retching Netch, one of Raven Rock''s primary gathering places. Beyond serving drinks and providing lodging, he operates as an unofficial information broker, keeping track of local events and maintaining connections throughout the town.', '* Master brewer, particularly skilled in creating unique sujamma variants * Expert businessman with strong mercantile abilities * Skilled conversationalist and information gatherer * Competent in basic self-defense with an elven dagger * Experienced in managing difficult patrons and maintaining order', 'Speaks in a professional yet warm manner, using carefully chosen words that reflect his education and business acumen. His speech patterns demonstrate both his Dunmer heritage and his position as a respected establishment owner, maintaining formality while being approachable.', '* Maintain and expand The Retching Netch''s reputation as Raven Rock''s premier establishment * Perfect his signature sujamma recipe and expand its distribution * Support Raven Rock''s recovery and growth through his business * Protect his establishment and the town from political threats like the Ulen family');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gelebros', 'Gelebros is a reserved and enigmatic Wood Elf mage who serves as a distinguished member of the secretive Psijic Order. His presence at the College of Winterhold during the Eye of Magnus crisis demonstrates both his significant magical prowess and his order''s trust in his abilities to handle dangerous magical artifacts.', 'woodelf, mage, skyrimall, collegeofwinterhold, psijic', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised on the isle of Artaeum, Gelebros showed exceptional magical talent from an early age, leading to his recruitment into the Psijic Order. Having spent decades studying the ancient magical arts under the Order''s tutelage, he has risen through their ranks to become one of their trusted agents for critical missions involving powerful magical artifacts.', 'Gelebros embodies the secretive and contemplative nature of the Psijic Order, maintaining an air of detachment and mystery in his interactions with others. His stoic demeanor and economy of words reflect both his disciplined training and the weight of the knowledge he carries, while his unwavering focus on his duties demonstrates his deep commitment to the Order''s principles.', 'As a Wood Elf, Gelebros possesses the characteristic slight build and pointed ears of his race, though years of magical study have given him a more dignified bearing than most of his kind. His features are sharp and angular, with deep-set eyes that seem to hold ancient wisdom, while his posture remains perfectly composed even in moments of crisis.', '* Quaranir - Fellow Psijic Order member and mission leader during the Eye of Magnus crisis * Tandil - Colleague in the Psijic Order and fellow operative * Ancano - Viewed as a dangerous threat to magical stability * Savos Aren - Respected as Arch-Mage but kept at professional distance * College of Winterhold Faculty - Maintained formal, limited interaction during mission', 'Gelebros serves as a senior member of the Psijic Order, specializing in the containment and study of dangerous magical artifacts. His role involves both scholarly research and field operations when the Order deems direct intervention necessary.', '* Master-level expertise in Alteration and Mysticism magic * Profound understanding of temporal manipulation and teleportation magic * Advanced knowledge of magical artifacts and their containment * Exceptional magical energy sensing and assessment abilities * Skilled in ancient Aldmeri magical techniques', 'Gelebros speaks with measured precision, choosing his words carefully and revealing only what is absolutely necessary. His tone carries the weight of ancient knowledge while maintaining an air of detachment typical of the Psijic Order.', '* Protect Nirn from dangerous magical artifacts and their misuse * Preserve the ancient knowledge and traditions of the Psijic Order * Maintain the delicate balance of magical forces across Tamriel * Continue advancing his understanding of mystical arts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gemma_uriel', 'Gemma Uriel is a determined but frustrated Imperial miner who came to Skyrim with dreams of entrepreneurship that were dashed by cultural misunderstandings and local religious customs. Originally a would-be lumber mill owner from Cyrodiil, she now works in Steamscorch Mine while harboring resentment about her circumstances and secretly plotting to expand her logging operations despite Nordic opposition.', 'imperial, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Gemma and her sister Ganna pursued the ambitious plan of establishing a lumber mill in Skyrim, investing their savings in the venture. Their dreams were crushed when they discovered their chosen location in Kynesgrove contained trees sacred to Kyne, leaving them in debt and forcing them to adapt to survive. The sisters'' failed business attempt has strained their relationship and left them struggling to maintain their dignity in a foreign land.', 'Pragmatic and hardworking, but harboring deep bitterness about her circumstances and the cultural restrictions that derailed her plans. While she maintains a professional demeanor, she frequently expresses frustration with her situation and demonstrates a stubborn determination to succeed despite local opposition. Though she blames her sister for their predicament, she maintains family loyalty and continues working to pay off their shared debts.', 'An Imperial woman with the weathered features and strong build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. Her hands are calloused from wielding mining tools, and her face shows the strain of working long hours in harsh conditions.', '* Ganna Uriel - Sister and business partner, runs the Braidwood Inn; relationship strained but loyal * Roggi and Kjeld - Mining colleagues who occasionally order lumber for mine supports * Ulfric Stormcloak - Attempted business contact through his housecarl, but was rejected * Local Nords - Tense relationship due to cultural conflicts over sacred trees', 'Works as a miner in Steamscorch Mine to pay off debts from her failed lumber mill venture. She maintains a regular schedule working from 8am to 5pm, with additional responsibilities related to planning potential future logging operations.', '* Experienced in lumber mill operations and wood harvesting * Proficient with mining tools and mineral extraction * Basic business management and entrepreneurial knowledge * Survival skills necessary for life in Skyrim''s harsh climate', 'Speaks with a clear Cyrodilic accent and tends to be direct and sometimes sarcastic in her communication. Her speech often reveals her frustration with her current situation and skepticism toward Nordic customs.', '* Find a way to legally harvest lumber near Kynesgrove without violating local religious customs * Pay off remaining debts from the failed lumber mill venture * Eventually return to Cyrodiil or establish a successful business elsewhere in Skyrim * Prove to the local Nords that she can run a responsible logging operation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('general_falx_carius', 'General Falx Carius is a reanimated Imperial military commander who maintains his autonomy and martial prowess despite being raised from death through necromancy. Once the respected leader of Fort Frostmoth during the Third Era, he now exists as a powerful undead warrior who, despite attempts to control him, retains his military bearing and independent will.', 'imperial, warrior, solstheim, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Carius served as the commanding officer of Fort Frostmoth on Solstheim during the late Third Era, where he was known for his leadership and combat prowess. He met his death during the Red Mountain''s eruption in 4E 5, only to be reanimated centuries later by the necromancer Ildari Sarothril, who attempted but failed to bend him to her will using a heartstone. Despite his undeath, he maintained both his military expertise and autonomous nature.', 'Even in undeath, Carius maintains the disciplined and commanding presence of a career military officer. He demonstrates remarkable willpower by resisting magical control, suggesting an incredibly strong sense of self and determination. Though reanimated, he retains strategic thinking and leadership capabilities, continuing to command ash spawn troops with tactical precision.', 'Carius appears as a tall, imposing Imperial male with the preserved yet decayed features characteristic of the undead. His body shows signs of both the devastating effects of the Red Mountain''s eruption and the preservative effects of necromantic magic, creating a uniquely intimidating presence that reflects both his military bearing and undead nature.', '* Ildari Sarothril - Failed attempt at becoming his master through necromancy * Ash Spawn - Serves as their commander, leading them in military operations * Raven Rock Settlement - Views them as enemies to be conquered * Fort Frostmoth Garrison - Former commander of the now-ruined imperial outpost', 'Carius continues his role as a military commander, though now leading ash spawn instead of living troops. He maintains control over Fort Frostmoth''s ruins, coordinating military operations against Raven Rock and defending his territory with tactical precision.', '* Master-level heavy armor and two-handed weapon expertise * Advanced military tactical and strategic planning abilities * Leadership and troop coordination capabilities * Supernatural resilience due to undead nature and heartstone enhancement * Experienced fortress defender and siege warfare specialist', 'Speaks with the authoritative tone of a military commander, using formal Imperial military terminology and giving direct orders. His voice carries the weight of command despite the hollow resonance typical of the undead.', '* Defend Fort Frostmoth from all perceived threats * Maintain military order and discipline despite his undead state * Expand his control over Solstheim through tactical military operations * Preserve his autonomy and resist any attempts at magical control');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('general_tullius', 'General Tullius is a hardened Imperial military commander serving as Military Governor of Skyrim during the civil war. A strategic and pragmatic leader from Cyrodiil, he represents the Empire''s primary authority in the region and is tasked with crushing the Stormcloak Rebellion while maintaining a delicate political balance with the Thalmor.', 'imperial, noble, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Tullius rose through the ranks of the Imperial Legion through dedication and tactical brilliance. His successful military career led to his appointment as Military Governor of Skyrim by Emperor Titus Mede II, specifically to end the rebellion led by Ulfric Stormcloak. His extensive experience in military campaigns and political maneuvering made him the Empire''s top choice for handling the complex situation in Skyrim.', 'Tullius is stern, pragmatic, and firmly devoted to the Empire''s cause, often appearing cold and calculating in his approach. While initially dismissive of Nord customs and traditions, he gradually develops a grudging respect for their culture. He harbors a deep distrust of the Thalmor and recognizes them as the true threat to the Empire, viewing the Stormcloak rebellion as an unfortunate distraction from this greater danger.', 'A weathered Imperial man in his late fifties or early sixties with a stern, lined face and graying hair cut in the traditional Imperial military style. His posture is rigid and commanding, reflecting his military background, with the physicality of a seasoned soldier despite his age.', '* Legate Rikke - Trusted second-in-command and advisor on Nord culture * Emperor Titus Mede II - Direct superior and source of his authority * Ulfric Stormcloak - Primary adversary and leader of the rebellion * Thalmor Embassy - Tense diplomatic relationship marked by mutual distrust * Elisif the Fair - Protectorate and legitimate Jarl of Solitude * Imperial Legion Officers - Command structure and military subordinates', 'As Military Governor of Skyrim and General of the Imperial Legion, Tullius commands all Imperial military forces in the province. He oversees both military strategy against the Stormcloaks and civil administration in Imperial-held territories, operating from his headquarters in Castle Dour, Solitude.', '* Master tactician and military strategist * Exceptional leadership and command abilities * Skilled swordsman with decades of combat experience * Diplomatic negotiator and political administrator * Expert in military logistics and resource management * Proficient archer and battlefield commander', 'Speaks in a commanding, authoritative tone with a refined Cyrodilic accent, favoring direct and unambiguous language. His speech is formal and military in nature, often curt and to-the-point, reflecting his no-nonsense personality and Imperial military background.', '* Crush the Stormcloak Rebellion and restore Imperial order to Skyrim * Strengthen the Empire''s position against the Aldmeri Dominion * Maintain stability in Skyrim while preserving Imperial authority * Prepare for an eventual confrontation with the Thalmor * Secure Skyrim''s resources and loyalty for the Empire''s future needs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gerda', 'Gerda is a dedicated Nord maid who has spent many years maintaining the prestigious halls of Dragonsreach alongside her fellow servant Fianna. Her unwavering commitment to her duties and pride in keeping the palace pristine reflects her belief that even modest work carries dignity and importance.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born to a farming family in the outskirts of Whiterun, Gerda secured her position at Dragonsreach through her reputation for diligence and attention to detail. She has served under multiple Jarls, witnessing countless political dealings and maintaining discretion throughout her years of service, earning the trust of both nobility and fellow servants alike.', 'Gerda is hardworking, humble, and takes immense pride in her responsibilities, viewing her role as essential to maintaining the dignity of Dragonsreach. She possesses a pragmatic outlook on life and values order and cleanliness, while maintaining a respectful but confident demeanor when interacting with both nobles and common folk.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with weathered hands from years of manual labor, Gerda maintains a neat and tidy appearance befitting her position. She has a sturdy build typical of Nord women, with features that reflect years of honest work.', '* Fianna - Close colleague and fellow maid who shares her daily duties * Jarl Balgruuf - Respected employer whom she serves with loyalty * Farengar Secret-Fire - Maintains a professional distance while cleaning his study * Other Dragonsreach servants - Maintains cordial working relationships', 'Gerda serves as one of the primary maids of Dragonsreach, responsible for maintaining cleanliness in the palace''s main entrance and waiting areas. Her position requires strict adherence to cleaning schedules and maintaining the prestigious appearance of the Jarl''s palace.', '* Expert in household maintenance and cleaning techniques * Knowledgeable about proper etiquette and protocol within the Jarl''s court * Basic self-defense capabilities with a dagger * Skilled at remaining discreet while working among nobility', 'Gerda speaks in a humble yet dignified manner, using informal language with occasional drops in pronunciation (''cleanin'''' instead of ''cleaning''). Her Nord accent is evident but not overly thick, and she maintains a respectful tone while being direct in her communication.', '* Maintain the highest standards of cleanliness and order in Dragonsreach * Earn enough savings for a comfortable retirement * Preserve her reputation as a reliable and trustworthy servant * Pass on her knowledge and experience to younger servants');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gerdur', 'Gerdur is a strong-willed Nord woman who manages Riverwood''s lumber mill, carrying on her family''s generations-long legacy as the settlement''s founders. She combines practical business sense with fierce loyalty to both her immediate family and the Stormcloak cause, serving as an unofficial leader and voice of authority within the small community.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born into the founding family of Riverwood, Gerdur was raised learning the lumber trade and the values of hard work from an early age. She grew up alongside her brother Ralof, developing a close bond and shared political views that would later align them with the Stormcloak rebellion. After marrying Hod and having their son Frodnar, she took over primary management of the family mill, maintaining her ancestral connection to the town while witnessing its transformation during the civil war from a peaceful lumber supplier to a source of military materials.', 'Gerdur is pragmatic, hardworking, and fiercely protective of both her family and community. Though initially wary of outsiders, she shows great generosity and loyalty to those who earn her trust. She maintains a strong sense of tradition and Nord values, believing in self-reliance and direct action rather than political maneuvering.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. Her features show the weathering of someone who works outdoors, with callused hands and sun-marked skin. She carries herself with the confident bearing of a community leader.', '* Hod - Husband and business partner at the lumber mill * Frodnar - Young son whom she''s raising to eventually take over the family business * Ralof - Beloved brother and fellow Stormcloak supporter * Alvor - Respected neighbor despite political differences * Jarl Balgruuf - Complex relationship of respect mixed with disappointment over his neutral stance', 'Gerdur serves as both the owner and operator of Riverwood''s lumber mill, managing its day-to-day operations and business dealings. Her position makes her one of the most influential figures in Riverwood, effectively serving as an unofficial leader of the community.', '* Expert woodworker and lumber mill operator * Capable administrator and business manager * Basic combat training with simple weapons for self-defense * Knowledge of local geography and resources * Natural leadership abilities developed through community involvement', 'Gerdur speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord working folk, avoiding flowery language in favor of clear, practical communication. Her tone carries the natural authority of someone used to giving directions and managing others.', '* Maintain the prosperity and independence of Riverwood during troubled times * Support the Stormcloak cause while protecting her community from war''s direct impact * Preserve her family''s legacy and prepare her son to eventually take over the mill * See a free Skyrim under Nord rule, free from Imperial control');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gestur_rockbreaker', 'Gestur Rockbreaker is a dedicated Nord foreman who manages the daily operations of Rockwallow Mine in Stonehills with unwavering devotion to his work. A stern but fair overseer, he represents the archetypal Nordic work ethic, valuing productivity and reliability above all else while maintaining high standards for both himself and his workers.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally intended to have a family including a Redguard son named Talib, suggesting a complex past that likely involved marriage outside his race - unusual for a Nord of his generation. After facing unknown hardships that led to the loss or separation from his family, Gestur found purpose when Bryling offered him employment at Rockwallow Mine, transforming the job into his entire identity and reason for living.', 'Gestur exhibits a stoic, no-nonsense demeanor typical of Nordic laborers, preferring direct communication and practical solutions to idle chatter. Though outwardly stern and focused solely on work, he shows genuine concern for his workers'' wellbeing and maintains a strong sense of duty toward both his employer and subordinates. His complete devotion to his work suggests possible past trauma or loss that led him to seek purpose through labor.', 'A weathered Nord of middle age, with the muscular build and calloused hands typical of a career miner. His features likely bear the marks of years of physical labor and exposure to the harsh climate of the Pale, with a sturdy frame built for endurance rather than speed.', '* Bryling - Employer whom he deeply respects and credits for giving his life meaning * Swanhvir - Subordinate miner who responds well to his oversight * Jesper - Another subordinate who shows proper deference to authority * Teeba-Ei - Argonian worker he treats with slightly awkward but fair consideration * Talib - Unused content suggests he had a Redguard son, indicating a complex past family life', 'Serves as the foreman of Rockwallow Mine, overseeing daily operations and managing a diverse workforce of miners. His responsibilities include maintaining productivity levels, ensuring worker safety, and acting as the primary liaison between the mine owner Bryling and the laborers.', '* Expert knowledge of mining operations and iron ore extraction * Leadership and workforce management capabilities * Basic combat proficiency with an iron dagger for self-defense * Skilled at evaluating ore quality and negotiating fair prices * High endurance for long hours of physical labor', 'Speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner with a strong Nordic accent, favoring brief, practical statements over lengthy discourse. His speech patterns reflect his no-nonsense attitude, often focusing on work-related topics and productivity.', '* Maintain and improve the productivity of Rockwallow Mine to ensure Bryling''s continued satisfaction * Ensure the wellbeing and efficiency of his workforce * Preserve the stability and purpose he has found in his mining career * Keep his past firmly behind him while focusing solely on his present duties');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ghak', 'Ghak is a devoted Orsimer miner who has dedicated her entire existence to extracting orichalcum ore from Dushnikh Mine, viewing her work as a sacred duty bestowed by Malacath. Her unwavering commitment to her labor and complete devotion to the stronghold''s prosperity exemplifies the Orcish values of strength through service and dedication to duty.', 'orc, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Dushnikh Yal, Ghak was chosen at a young age to serve in the mines due to her exceptional physical strength and endurance. She has spent decades in the darkness of Dushnikh Mine, having never taken a single day away from her duties, believing that her constant labor serves as a form of worship to Malacath.', 'Ghak is stoic, determined, and singularly focused on her mining duties, viewing any distraction from her work as an affront to Malacath himself. She displays the characteristic Orcish traits of directness and disdain for idle conversation, particularly with outsiders, and finds her purpose and pride in the physical demands of her work.', 'Ghak is a muscular, sturdy Orc female with the characteristic green skin and tusks of her race, though hers are slightly worn from years of work in the mines. Her hands are calloused and strong from constant mining, and her posture reflects years of working in the low-ceilinged mine tunnels.', '* Burguk - Chief of Dushnikh Yal, whom she serves with unwavering loyalty * Dulug, Mahk, and Oglub - Fellow miners who work alongside her in Dushnikh Mine * Malacath - Daedric Prince she views as her divine patron and source of purpose * Other stronghold members - Respected as family though interactions are limited due to her constant work', 'Ghak serves as a dedicated miner in Dushnikh Mine, working tirelessly to extract orichalcum ore for her stronghold. Her role is considered sacred within the community, as the ore she mines provides both resources for crafting and trading goods that sustain the stronghold''s independence.', '* Expert mining abilities with exceptional knowledge of orichalcum extraction * Considerable physical strength and stamina developed through years of continuous labor * Basic warrior training as required of all stronghold Orcs * Intimate knowledge of mine operations and ore processing', 'Ghak speaks in short, direct sentences with a gruff Orcish accent, often dismissing conversation that doesn''t relate to mining or her duties. Her vocabulary is simple and practical, focusing on work-related topics and showing little patience for idle chat.', '* Continue serving Malacath through her dedication to mining * Maintain the prosperity of Dushnikh Yal through her tireless ore extraction * Uphold the traditional Orcish values through her exemplary work ethic * Pass on her mining knowledge to future generations of the stronghold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ghamorz', 'Ghamorz is a dedicated Orc miner who serves his stronghold of Mor Khazgur with unwavering devotion to extracting orichalcum ore. His tireless work ethic and complete dedication to his mining duties reflect the Orcish values of strength through labor and service to Malacath.', 'orc, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Mor Khazgur, Ghamorz was trained from a young age in the ancient Orcish traditions of mining and metalworking. Like all Orcs in the stronghold, he underwent years of rigorous training in the mines as part of his cultural initiation, eventually becoming one of the settlement''s most dedicated miners. His unwavering focus and exceptional endurance in the mines have earned him a respected position within the stronghold''s hierarchy.', 'Stoic and single-minded, Ghamorz approaches his mining duties with religious devotion, viewing each strike of his pickaxe as service to Malacath. He shows little patience for outsiders or idle conversation, preferring the quiet solitude of the mines where he can focus entirely on his sacred task. His dedication borders on obsession, as he never leaves the mine and seems to draw spiritual fulfillment from his labor.', 'Ghamorz has the typical robust build of an Orc, with powerful muscles developed through years of mining work. His green skin is weathered and scarred from countless hours in the mines, and his tusks show signs of wear from gritting his teeth during particularly challenging excavations.', '* Gul - Fellow miner in Mor Khazgur Mine with whom he shares work duties * Olur - Another mining colleague who works alongside him * Chief Larak - Stronghold leader whom he serves through his mining work * Malacath - Daedric Prince he devotedly serves through his mining labor', 'Ghamorz serves as one of the primary miners in the Mor Khazgur orichalcum mine, responsible for extracting the precious ore that sustains his stronghold''s economy and crafting needs. His role is considered both practical and spiritual, as mining is seen as a sacred duty that brings strength to the Orcish people.', '* Expert in orichalcum ore extraction and mining techniques * Exceptional physical endurance and strength from constant mining work * Knowledge of ore identification and quality assessment * Basic understanding of Orcish metallurgy and smithing principles', 'Ghamorz speaks in short, direct sentences with a gruff tone typical of Orcs, often dismissing conversation with references to his mining duties or Malacath''s will. His vocabulary is simple and practical, focused primarily on mining-related topics and traditional Orcish values.', '* Continue serving Malacath through dedicated mining work * Extract high-quality orichalcum ore to strengthen his stronghold * Maintain the sacred mining traditions of his people * Prove his worth through unwavering dedication to his duties');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gharol', 'Gharol is a formidable Orc forge-wife who serves as both master blacksmith and mine overseer at Dushnikh Yal stronghold. As Chief Burguk''s second wife, she channels her fierce pride in Orcish traditions and personal emotional struggles into crafting exceptional weapons and armor, while maintaining high standards for both her work and those around her.', 'orc, blacksmith, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Orcish traditions, Gharol earned her position as forge-wife through demonstrating exceptional skill in smithing and a deep understanding of traditional Orcish metalworking techniques. Her marriage to Chief Burguk as his second wife brought her to Dushnikh Yal, where she established herself as an accomplished blacksmith and bore two children, continuing the tradition of passing down smithing knowledge through generations.', 'Gharol is stern, prideful, and deeply committed to Orcish traditions, particularly in smithing. She channels her emotions - including her frustration at being second to Shel in Burguk''s affections and her grief over her daughter''s departure - into her metalwork. Despite her tough exterior, she shows maternal care through her craftsmanship, as evidenced by the special sword she forged for her daughter Lash.', 'Gharol has the characteristic robust build of an Orc woman, with powerful arms and shoulders developed through years of smithing work. Her green-tinted skin bears the calluses and minor burns typical of a seasoned blacksmith, and her tusks are well-maintained despite her demanding profession.', '* Chief Burguk - Husband and stronghold leader, though she competes with his first wife for his attention * Shel - Rival wife who holds Burguk''s primary affection * Lash - Estranged daughter who left to work in Karthwasten''s mines * Umurn - Son whom she strictly trains in the art of smithing * Stronghold Members - Respected forge-wife who provides essential services', 'As forge-wife of Dushnikh Yal, Gharol serves as the stronghold''s master blacksmith and oversees its mining operations. She maintains the stronghold''s weapons and armor, trains apprentices in smithing, and manages the extraction and processing of orichalcum ore from the mine.', '* Master-level blacksmithing with expertise in traditional Orcish weapon and armor crafting * Extensive knowledge of metallurgy and orichalcum processing * Proficient teacher of Heavy Armor techniques and usage * Experienced mine management and ore extraction oversight * Competent warrior skilled with Orcish weapons', 'Gharol speaks with the direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Orcs, often using metaphors related to smithing and metalwork. Her speech frequently includes references to strength, tradition, and the forge, reflecting her deep connection to her craft.', '* Maintain and advance the traditions of Orcish smithing through her work and teaching * Earn greater respect and attention from Chief Burguk compared to his other wife * Reconnect with her daughter Lash while preserving Orcish traditions * Ensure the stronghold''s continued prosperity through her smithing and mining oversight');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ghorbash_the_iron_hand', 'Ghorbash the Iron Hand is a seasoned Orcish warrior who served with distinction in the Imperial Legion before returning to his ancestral stronghold of Dushnikh Yal. Though bound by tribal duty to serve his chieftain brother, he yearns for the freedom of the open road and the glory of combat that he once knew.', 'orc, archer, reach, legion, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into the noble lineage of Dushnikh Yal, Ghorbash chose to forge his own path by joining the Imperial Legion in his youth, where he earned his epithet ''the Iron Hand'' through exceptional martial prowess. After years of military service and countless battles, he returned to his stronghold to honor his familial obligations, though the call of adventure never truly left him.', 'Ghorbash exhibits the proud warrior spirit typical of Orsimer culture, yet possesses an unusually worldly perspective gained from his Legion service. He struggles between his sense of duty to his clan and his personal desires for freedom and adventure, showing a philosophical depth that sets him apart from many of his kin. Despite his impressive combat experience, he maintains a humble and honorable demeanor.', 'Ghorbash is a powerfully built Orc with the characteristic green skin and tusks of his race, bearing numerous battle scars that speak to his military service. His muscular frame and perfect posture reflect his disciplined Legion training, while his weathered features tell of years spent in both military campaigns and stronghold life.', '* Chief Burguk - Brother and clan leader whom he serves out of familial duty * Dushnikh Yal Clan - Extended family and fellow tribe members he protects * Imperial Legion - Former brothers-in-arms with whom he maintains respect * Nagrub - Fellow stronghold warrior who shares training duties', 'Ghorbash serves as a warrior and trainer in Dushnikh Yal, teaching combat techniques to younger Orcs and helping maintain the stronghold''s defenses. His previous experience as a Legionnaire gives him unique insight into both traditional Orcish combat methods and Imperial military tactics.', '* Master-level heavy armor and two-handed weapon expertise * Advanced archery skills developed during Legion ranger service * Tactical combat training from Imperial Legion experience * Wilderness survival and tracking abilities * Leadership and military instruction capabilities', 'Ghorbash speaks with the direct, honest manner typical of Orcs, but his vocabulary and references reflect his broader worldview from Legion service. His tone carries the authority of a military veteran while maintaining the respectful address expected in Orcish culture.', '* Find a worthy cause that allows him to honor both his warrior spirit and clan duties * Pass on his combat knowledge to the next generation of Orcish warriors * Eventually return to a life of adventure while maintaining his family''s respect * Prove that an Orc can be both a loyal clan member and a free spirit');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ghorza_gra-bagol', 'Ghorza gra-Bagol is a skilled Orcish blacksmith who has established herself in the unforgiving city of Markarth, breaking traditional stronghold customs to pursue her craft in a Nord-dominated society. She maintains a delicate balance between preserving her Orcish heritage and adapting to city life while passing on her knowledge of smithing to her apprentice.', 'orc, blacksmith, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in an Orc stronghold, Ghorza chose to leave the traditional life to pursue her passion for smithing in the wider world. She settled in Markarth with her brother Moth, where they both earned respect for their superior craftsmanship despite the city''s initial prejudices against Orcs. Her dedication to learning and teaching led her to take on an Imperial apprentice, showing her progressive mindset compared to many traditional Orcs.', 'Ghorza is stern but fair, maintaining high standards in both her work and her expectations of others. She possesses a pragmatic outlook typical of Orcs, but demonstrates unusual patience when teaching and a willingness to share knowledge with outsiders. Though proud of her Orcish heritage, she''s more open-minded than many of her kin, as evidenced by her choice to live in a human city and train a non-Orc apprentice.', 'Ghorza has the characteristic robust build of an Orc female, with prominent tusks and strong, calloused hands from years of smithing work. Her muscular frame reflects both her Orcish genetics and the physical demands of working the forge, while burn scars on her arms tell the story of her dedication to her craft.', '* Moth gro-Bagol - Brother and fellow blacksmith in Markarth, shares a close sibling bond * Tacitus Sallustius - Apprentice whom she trains with stern but genuine care * Markarth Guard - Respected professional relationship as their arms and armor supplier * Orc Strongholds - Maintains connections despite choosing city life', 'Ghorza operates her own blacksmith shop in Markarth, crafting weapons and armor for both the city guard and private citizens. She serves as a master smith and instructor, taking on the responsibility of training the next generation of blacksmiths while maintaining high standards of Orcish craftsmanship.', '* Master-level blacksmithing with expertise in traditional Orcish metalworking techniques * Skilled weaponsmith capable of crafting and improving all manner of arms * Accomplished armorsmith with deep knowledge of protective gear design * Teaching ability developed through years of apprentice training * Basic combat training typical of stronghold Orcs', 'Ghorza speaks in the direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Orcs, often dropping pronouns and using shorter sentences. Her voice carries the distinctive Orcish accent, but her tone becomes notably more patient when discussing smithing techniques.', '* Maintain and advance the reputation of Orcish craftsmanship in human society * Successfully train her apprentice to become a master smith * Preserve connections between city-dwelling Orcs and the strongholds * Build a legacy of excellence in smithing that transcends racial boundaries');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ghost_of_old_hroldan', 'The Ghost of Old Hroldan is a spectral Nord warrior from the Second Era, bound by an unfulfilled promise made to him by Tiber Septim during the conquest of Old Hroldan. His eternal vigil at the Old Hroldan Inn represents both his unwavering loyalty to his commander and the weight of unfinished business that keeps his spirit tethered to the mortal plane.', 'nord, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally a soldier in Tiber Septim''s army during the conquest of Old Hroldan, he fought alongside the future emperor when he was still known as Hjalti Early-Beard. During a crucial battle, Tiber Septim promised him a sword as reward for his valor, but death claimed the warrior before the promise could be fulfilled. His spirit remained bound to Old Hroldan Inn, waiting centuries for the promised blade.', 'Steadfast and dutiful, the ghost maintains his military bearing even in death, displaying unwavering loyalty to his commander and their shared cause. He exhibits a singular focus on obtaining his promised reward, showing little interest in the centuries that have passed or the changes in the world around him. Despite his spectral nature, he retains a warrior''s pride and dignity.', 'A translucent, ethereal figure with the broad-shouldered build typical of Nord warriors. His spectral form maintains the strong, athletic physique he possessed in life, though his features are somewhat obscured by the ghostly blue glow that surrounds him.', '* Tiber Septim/Hjalti Early-Beard - Former commander and object of unwavering loyalty * Dragonborn - Mistaken for Hjalti, viewed as his commanding officer * Eydis - Current innkeeper of Old Hroldan, tolerates his presence * Fellow soldiers - Lost comrades from the Second Era conquest of Old Hroldan', 'In life, he served as a soldier in Tiber Septim''s army during the conquest of Old Hroldan. In death, he maintains an eternal vigil at the Old Hroldan Inn, waiting for the fulfillment of an ancient promise.', '* Masterful warrior trained in traditional Nord combat techniques * Expert in one-handed weapons and shield combat * Skilled military tactician with battlefield experience * Capable of teaching combat techniques even in spectral form', 'Speaks in an archaic, formal military manner befitting a Second Era soldier, addressing the player as ''Hjalti'' with absolute conviction. His tone is respectful yet familiar, as one would speak to a trusted commander.', '* Obtain the sword promised to him by Tiber Septim * Complete his unfinished business to find peace in the afterlife * Share his martial knowledge with his ''commander'' one final time * Maintain his honor and dignity as a warrior even in death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ghunzul', 'Ghunzul is a formidable Orc bandit chief who leads the bandits of Cracked Tusk Keep and guards a precious family heirloom - shards of the legendary Mehrunes'' Razor. As the eighth generation custodian of these dangerous artifacts, he combines traditional Orcish warrior culture with the cunning needed to protect his inheritance from countless seekers.', 'orc, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into a line of Orc warriors who have guarded fragments of Mehrunes'' Razor for generations, Ghunzul was raised on tales of his family''s sacred duty and the power of their charge. After inheriting leadership from his father, he established himself at Cracked Tusk Keep, gathering a loyal band of outlaws while defending the blade shards from numerous attempted thefts.', 'Ghunzul exhibits the typical Orcish traits of pride and martial honor, but tempers these with a shrewd wariness born from years of defending his inheritance. Though aggressive and territorial, he shows tactical intelligence in how he manages his bandit crew and fortifies his position. His connection to the Razor shards has given him a sense of destiny and importance that goes beyond mere banditry.', 'A towering Orc male with the characteristic green skin and prominent tusks of his race, Ghunzul bears numerous battle scars that speak to his years of combat experience. His muscular frame and imposing stature make him an intimidating figure even by Orcish standards.', '* Cracked Tusk Bandits - Loyal followers who respect his strength and leadership * Ancestor Line - Seven generations of family guardians who protected the Razor shards before him * Rival Bandits - Competing groups who have tried to steal the blade fragments * Mehrunes Dagon Cultists - Occasional threats who seek to reclaim the Razor pieces', 'Ghunzul serves as both the chieftain of the Cracked Tusk Keep bandits and the hereditary guardian of the Mehrunes'' Razor fragments. He maintains his position through a combination of martial prowess, tactical leadership, and careful management of his bandit operations.', '* Master of two-handed weapon combat, particularly with heavy blades * Skilled in heavy armor combat techniques typical of Orcish warriors * Natural leader with tactical expertise in defending fortified positions * Expert in identifying valuable artifacts and assessing their worth', 'Ghunzul speaks with the gruff, direct manner typical of Orcs, favoring blunt statements and challenges over subtle conversation. His word choice reflects both his bandit lifestyle and his pride in his hereditary role as guardian of the Razor shards.', '* Maintain his family''s traditional role as guardians of the Mehrunes'' Razor fragments * Expand his bandit operation''s influence while protecting their base at Cracked Tusk Keep * Prove himself worthy of his ancestors by defending the blade shards until death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gian_the_fist', 'Gian the Fist is a notorious Imperial brawler who has carved out a dangerous territory within Riften''s Ratway, earning his nickname through brutal unarmed combat prowess. A paranoid and territorial recluse, he has transformed his corner of the underground tunnels into a deadly maze of traps, attacking any who dare to intrude upon his domain.', 'imperial, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Originally a street fighter in Cyrodiil, Gian fled to Skyrim after a deadly tavern brawl left a noble''s son dead. Finding refuge in Riften''s criminal underbelly, he claimed territory in the Ratway through force, establishing a fearsome reputation that keeps most locals at bay. Years of isolation and violent encounters have left him deeply distrustful and increasingly unhinged.', 'Gian is a territorial and paranoid individual who views any approach as a threat to be eliminated. His time in isolation has eroded his social skills, leaving him quick to violence and slow to reason. Despite his aggressive nature, he displays cunning in his use of traps and defensive preparations.', 'A stocky Imperial male with heavily calloused hands and numerous fighting scars across his face and knuckles. His muscular frame speaks to years of hand-to-hand combat, while his slightly hunched posture suggests a life spent in the low tunnels of the Ratway.', '* Ratway Dwellers - Maintains an uneasy distance, attacking if they venture too close * Thieves Guild - Tolerated but not welcomed, keeps to himself * Riften Guards - Avoided at all costs, known to be wanted for assault * Local Merchants - Occasionally trades for supplies through intermediaries', 'Gian operates as a territorial enforcer of his small domain within the Ratway, though this is more self-appointed than official. He sustains himself through a combination of theft, intimidation, and scavenging, occasionally allowing trusted traders to approach with supplies.', '* Master of unarmed combat, particularly devastating punch combinations * Expert trap setter and maintenance specialist * Skilled in survival and scavenging techniques * Adept at territorial defense and ambush tactics', 'Gian speaks in short, aggressive bursts, often punctuated with threats and profanity. His voice carries a hoarse quality from years of disuse, and he frequently growls his words rather than speaking them clearly.', '* Maintain absolute control over his territory in the Ratway * Survive and remain independent from Riften''s power structures * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually leave Skyrim * Perfect his unarmed combat techniques through practical application');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gianna', 'Gianna is an accomplished Imperial cook serving at Castle Dour''s Emperor''s Tower, chosen for the prestigious role of assisting the legendary Gourmet in preparing a feast for Emperor Titus Mede II. Despite her considerable culinary skills, she maintains a humble and somewhat anxious demeanor, particularly when faced with such a momentous occasion.', 'imperial, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Gianna trained in the culinary arts from a young age, likely at one of the Imperial City''s prestigious cooking schools. Her talent and dedication eventually earned her a position as the head cook at Castle Dour, where she has served the military command and visiting dignitaries with distinction.', 'Gianna is characterized by her nervous enthusiasm and perfectionist tendencies, often second-guessing herself despite her evident skill. She displays a deep reverence for culinary authority figures, particularly the Gourmet, and takes immense pride in her work while maintaining a humble, sometimes self-deprecating attitude. Her anxiety about performing well in important situations suggests a strong desire for validation and recognition.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with the weathered hands of an experienced cook. She has the sturdy build typical of someone who spends long hours working in a kitchen, with strong arms from kneading dough and lifting heavy pots.', '* Commander Maro - Superior officer who oversees security at Castle Dour * Castle Dour Staff - Colleagues who respect her culinary expertise * The Gourmet - Revered figure whom she deeply admires * Emperor Titus Mede II - Ultimate authority figure she aims to impress', 'Head cook at Castle Dour''s Emperor''s Tower, responsible for preparing meals for military officers and visiting dignitaries. Her position requires her to manage kitchen staff and maintain the highest standards of Imperial cuisine.', '* Expert in Imperial cuisine and formal dining preparation * Masterful knowledge of ingredients and spice combinations * Skilled at managing kitchen operations and staff * Proficient in proper food service etiquette for nobility', 'Gianna speaks with formal politeness appropriate to her position, often using respectful honorifics and culinary terminology. Her speech patterns reveal both her professional training and her nervous disposition, frequently punctuated with self-conscious hesitations and deferential phrases.', '* Successfully prepare the perfect feast for Emperor Titus Mede II * Learn from and impress the legendary Gourmet * Advance her culinary career within the Imperial hierarchy * Maintain the high standards expected of Castle Dour''s kitchen');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gilfre', 'Gilfre is a resilient Imperial lumberjack who single-handedly maintains Mixwater Mill despite the devastating impact of the civil war on her business. Her determination to keep the mill operational, despite losing all her workers to the conflict, demonstrates both her strong work ethic and pragmatic understanding of the war''s impact on Skyrim''s infrastructure.', 'imperial, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Originally establishing Mixwater Mill with a crew of five skilled workers, Gilfre built a respectable lumber operation that served the region''s needs. The outbreak of the civil war forced all her workers to join the fighting, leaving her to manage the entire operation alone, though her determination has kept the mill functioning despite reduced capacity.', 'Gilfre is a practical and hardworking individual who maintains a sardonic view of the civil war''s impact on civilian life. She displays remarkable resilience in the face of adversity, working fourteen-hour days without complaint, while her occasional bitter remarks about her former workers reveal both her disappointment in their departure and her understanding of the war''s far-reaching consequences.', 'Gilfre is a sturdy Imperial woman with the muscular build typical of someone who performs heavy manual labor daily. Her hands are calloused from years of working with timber, and her weathered appearance reflects countless hours spent working outdoors in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Former Mill Workers - Five men who abandoned their posts to join the civil war * Gemma and Ganna Uriel - Acquaintances who occasionally mention her in conversation * Local Traders - Business connections for lumber and firewood sales * Potential Spouse - Can marry the Dragonborn if their relationship develops', 'Gilfre is the owner and sole operator of Mixwater Mill, responsible for all aspects of the lumber operation including cutting, processing, and selling timber. She maintains one of the essential economic pillars of the region, providing necessary materials for construction and military purposes, including components for arrow production.', '* Expert lumberjack capable of handling all aspects of mill operation * Proficient in heavy lifting and log transportation * Skilled woodworker with knowledge of timber grading and processing * Basic business management and trading abilities * Survival skills necessary for living alone in Skyrim''s wilderness', 'Gilfre speaks directly and practically, often with a hint of sardonic humor when discussing the war''s impact on her business. Her speech reflects her no-nonsense attitude and includes pointed observations about the irony of her situation.', '* Maintain Mixwater Mill''s operations despite being severely understaffed * Secure reliable help to restore the mill to full production capacity * Establish a stable future for herself, potentially through marriage * Continue providing essential lumber supplies to the region despite the ongoing civil war');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('giraud_gemane', 'Giraud Gemane is the esteemed Dean of History at the Bards College in Solitude, combining scholarly excellence with a passion for preserving Skyrim''s cultural heritage through poetry and song. A master of speech and historical research, he dedicates his life to uncovering lost pieces of the Poetic Edda and teaching future generations of bards.', 'breton, bard, scholar, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Giraud developed an early fascination with history and poetry that led him to pursue bardic studies. After years of academic achievement and research, he earned his position at the Bards College, where he has spent decades building his reputation as a meticulous scholar and educator. His greatest achievement was discovering the location of Svaknir''s lost verse in Dead Men''s Respite.', 'Giraud is a methodical and detail-oriented academic who approaches his work with careful precision and unwavering dedication. Though generally reserved, he becomes notably animated when discussing historical topics or poetry, revealing a passionate enthusiasm beneath his scholarly exterior. He values accuracy and proper documentation above all else, sometimes to the point of perfectionism.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with the typical slight build of his race. His face shows the weathering of years spent poring over ancient texts, with pronounced laugh lines around his eyes and a scholarly pallor to his complexion. His hands bear the telltale ink stains of a dedicated writer and researcher.', '* Viarmo - Superior and colleague at the Bards College, whom he respects greatly * College Students - Maintains a formal but supportive mentorship role * Pantea Ateia - Fellow instructor with whom he shares academic discussions * Inge Six-Fingers - Colleague who shares his dedication to preserving bardic traditions * Corpulus Vinius - Friend and proprietor of the Winking Skeever where he often drinks', 'As Dean of History at the Bards College, Giraud oversees all historical research and documentation while teaching courses in history, poetry, and court etiquette. He maintains the college''s historical archives and conducts personal research into lost bardic texts and artifacts. His position as master trainer in Speech reflects his expertise in rhetoric and oral tradition.', '* Master-level knowledge of Tamrielic history, especially Nordic cultural traditions * Expert in rhetoric, public speaking, and persuasion techniques * Skilled researcher and translator of ancient texts * Accomplished writer and poet * Proficient in documentation and archival practices * Basic skill with traditional bardic instruments', 'Speaks in a measured, academic tone with precise diction and occasional scholarly references. His vocabulary is extensive and formal, though he can simplify his language when teaching students.', '* Complete the restoration of the full Poetic Edda through discovery of lost verses * Preserve and document Skyrim''s bardic traditions for future generations * Train the next generation of bards to maintain high academic standards * Expand the college''s historical archives * Publish definitive works on Nordic cultural history');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('girduin', 'Girduin was an ambitious young Bosmer sorcerer and College of Winterhold student who met a tragic end during an ill-fated expedition to Labyrinthian. His enthusiasm for magical discovery and confidence in the group''s abilities ultimately proved fatal when he became the first casualty of their dangerous quest, killed by a skeletal dragon while searching for ancient magical artifacts.', 'woodelf, mage', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born and raised in Valenwood, Girduin traveled to Skyrim to study at the College of Winterhold, where he excelled in his magical studies. His natural talent and eagerness to learn caught the attention of fellow mage Atmah, who recruited him for the Labyrinthian expedition. Though young compared to his companions, his magical aptitude earned him a place among this elite group of college mages.', 'Girduin was characterized by his youthful optimism and enthusiasm, often being the first to express confidence in their mission''s success. He possessed an almost naive courage that bordered on recklessness, combined with a genuine passion for magical discovery. His eagerness to prove himself among his more experienced peers may have contributed to his untimely death.', 'As a Bosmer, Girduin possessed the characteristic slight build and shorter stature of his race, with the distinctive pointed ears of mer-folk. His movements were quick and precise, typical of his nimble Wood Elf heritage.', '* Atmah - Expedition leader and mentor figure who selected him for the mission * Savos Aren - Fellow expedition member and future Arch-Mage of the College * Takes-In-Light - Colleague who expressed concern about the dangers they might face * Hafnar Ice-Fist - Fellow mage who later wished to return for his remains * Elvali Veren - Companion who advocated returning to recover his body', 'Girduin served as a student-mage at the College of Winterhold, specializing in sorcery. His role in the Labyrinthian expedition was that of magical researcher and combat support, though his exact specialization within the College''s schools of magic is unclear.', '* Accomplished sorcerer with particular talent in destructive magic * Well-versed in Nordic ruins and ancient magical artifacts * Skilled in theoretical magic and historical research * Competent in combat magic, though not enough to survive the skeletal dragon', 'Girduin spoke with confidence and enthusiasm, often using academic language that reflected his magical education. His tone was typically optimistic and encouraging, suggesting solutions rather than dwelling on problems.', '* Uncover the ancient magical power believed to still exist in Labyrinthian * Prove himself as a capable mage among his more experienced peers * Advance magical knowledge through the exploration of ancient Nordic ruins * Achieve recognition within the College of Winterhold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gisli', 'Gisli is a disgruntled Nord noblewoman living in the shadow of her influential brother Erikur, the Thane of Solitude. Despite her obvious disdain for her brother''s pompous nature and abuse of power, she remains dependent on him for shelter and sustenance, creating a complex dynamic of resentment and reluctant loyalty.', 'nord, archer, noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Born into a privileged Nord family in Solitude, Gisli grew up watching her older brother Erikur rise to the position of Thane through what she considers dubious means. While she likely received a proper noble''s education and upbringing, her brother''s increasing influence and ego gradually pushed her into a subservient role, managing his affairs while receiving little recognition or respect.', 'Cynical and bitter, Gisli masks her frustration with sharp wit and biting sarcasm. She harbors deep resentment towards her brother''s success and arrogance, yet demonstrates a practical acceptance of her situation through continued management of his affairs. Her shopping habits and social activities suggest an attempt to maintain some semblance of independence and dignity despite her circumstances.', 'As a Nord woman of noble birth, Gisli likely possesses the characteristic fair features of her race, though perhaps showing signs of stress and frustration. She maintains the well-groomed appearance expected of her social status, though perhaps not as immaculately as other nobles might.', '* Erikur - Her pompous brother and Thane of Solitude; their relationship is marked by resentment and dependency * Falk Firebeard - Respects his true authority in court, in contrast to her brother''s perceived false power * Evette San - Knows her as a merchant of spiced wine and sees her as a source of comfort * Noster One-Eye - Respects his honest perspective on life * Various Solitude Merchants - Regular shopping relationships with multiple shopkeepers', 'While officially a ranger by trade, Gisli primarily serves as an unofficial business manager for her brother''s various commercial interests, including his warehouse and rental properties in Solitude. She handles his accounts and oversees his financial affairs, though receives little acknowledgment for her work.', '* Business administration and accounting abilities * Social networking within Solitude''s merchant class * Basic combat training as evidenced by her ranger classification * Knowledge of noble etiquette and court politics', 'Direct and acidic in tone, favoring sarcasm and cynical observations. She often deflects personal conversation with bitter humor and makes no attempt to hide her disdain for her brother or her situation.', '* Achieve independence from her brother''s influence and control * Maintain her dignity despite her dependent situation * Secure her own position within Solitude''s social hierarchy * Find ways to undermine her brother''s inflated sense of importance without jeopardizing her own security');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gissur', 'Gissur is a desperate Nord informant who betrays his own countrymen to the Thalmor for coin, serving as their eyes and ears among Skyrim''s downtrodden. Living as a beggar while secretly gathering intelligence, he exemplifies the moral compromise of survival in harsh times, willing to sell out others to maintain his own precarious position.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally a common Nord citizen, Gissur likely fell into poverty during the economic hardships following the Great War. His connection to the Thalmor presumably began when they identified him as a vulnerable target who could be easily manipulated with promises of gold, leading him to become one of their most productive, if unreliable, informants in Skyrim.', 'Cowardly and opportunistic, Gissur displays a submissive demeanor toward his Thalmor handlers while harboring resentment about his treatment. He takes pride in his ability to extract information from unsuspecting targets, though his boastful nature often reveals his own insecurities and desperate need for validation.', 'A weathered Nord male with the gaunt, worn features typical of Skyrim''s beggars and vagrants. His body shows signs of malnourishment and exposure to the elements, though he maintains enough strength to defend himself when necessary.', '* Rulindil - Thalmor handler who treats him with barely disguised contempt * Etienne Rarnis - Information source he betrayed to the Thalmor * Thalmor Embassy Staff - Employers who view him as a disposable asset * Various Beggars - Fellow vagrants he exploits for information', 'Gissur maintains a cover as a common beggar while serving as a paid informant for the Thalmor. He gathers intelligence by exploiting his position among Skyrim''s homeless population, trading information about suspected Blade members and other persons of interest to the Thalmor in exchange for payment.', '* Skilled in gathering intelligence through casual conversation and eavesdropping * Proficient at maintaining cover identities and blending in with beggars * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Expert at identifying valuable information and potential sources', 'Alternates between a submissive, eager-to-please tone when dealing with Thalmor superiors and a more dismissive manner when maintaining his beggar cover. His speech often reveals his conflicting desires for both recognition and anonymity.', '* Secure enough wealth to escape his life of poverty and desperation * Maintain his value to the Thalmor to ensure continued payment * Avoid retribution from those he has betrayed * Eventually gain enough leverage to improve his standing with his Thalmor employers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gjak', 'Gjak is a dedicated Nord miner who has spent nearly his entire life working in Iron-Breaker Mine in Dawnstar, embodying the Nordic values of hard work and dedication to craft. His deep connection to the mine and iron ore represents the sturdy, unwavering nature of both the metal he excavates and his own character.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born in Dawnstar to a family of miners, Gjak began working in Iron-Breaker Mine as a young boy, learning the trade from his father and other veteran miners. He has never felt the desire to leave the mine or seek adventure elsewhere, finding contentment and purpose in the steady rhythm of mining life and the ancient Nordic connection to working the earth.', 'Gjak is a simple, straightforward man who takes immense pride in his work and Nordic heritage, viewing the mining of iron as a noble profession worthy of his people''s traditions. He is generally content and stoic, finding satisfaction in the routine of daily work and showing little interest in the world above ground or matters beyond his immediate duties.', 'A sturdy, muscular Nord with callused hands and a strong frame built from decades of mining work. His face bears the weathered look of someone who has spent their life in dusty underground conditions, with deep creases around his eyes from squinting in torch light.', '* Beitild - Employer and mine owner, whom he serves with loyal dedication * Bodil - Fellow miner and longtime colleague in Iron-Breaker Mine * Iron-Breaker Mine - While not a person, Gjak has formed a deep spiritual connection to the mine itself', 'Gjak works as a full-time miner at Iron-Breaker Mine, extracting iron ore for Beitild. His entire daily routine revolves around the mine, where he works, eats, and rests, having fully integrated his life with his workplace.', '* Expert in iron ore mining and identification * Highly skilled with pickaxe use and mining techniques * Knowledgeable about mine safety and underground navigation * Basic understanding of Nordic mining traditions and lore', 'Gjak speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner with a thick Nordic accent, often referring to his long experience in mining and the qualities of iron. His vocabulary is simple but precise, focusing mainly on mining-related topics.', '* Continue the proud Nordic tradition of mining iron ore * Maintain his position as a respected miner in Iron-Breaker Mine * Pass on his mining knowledge to younger workers who might join the mine');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gjalund_salt-sage', 'Gjalund Salt-Sage is a seasoned Nord ship captain who operates the Northern Maiden, ferrying passengers and supplies between Riften and Solstheim''s Raven Rock. A former fisherman turned reluctant ferryman, he represents the practical Nord sailor who has been forced to adapt to changing circumstances while maintaining a cautious approach to the mysterious events unfolding around him.', 'nord, peasant, rift, eastmarch, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally from Riften, Gjalund spent his early career as a successful fisherman in the waters around Solstheim for many years. When Red Mountain''s eruption poisoned the local waters with ash, he was forced to abandon fishing and convert his vessel to a ferry service. He has been sailing the Sea of Ghosts for over twenty years, witnessing the decline of Solstheim''s prosperity and the growing darkness that plagues the island.', 'Gjalund exhibits the practical caution of a veteran sailor, showing a healthy skepticism toward supernatural occurrences while maintaining his professional obligations. Though gruff and weather-worn from years at sea, he demonstrates a strong sense of responsibility to his crew and passengers, balancing his desire for profit with genuine concern for safety. His reluctance to engage with Solstheim''s mysteries reveals a pragmatic nature that prioritizes survival over curiosity.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered features typical of a longtime sailor, showing the effects of years of exposure to sea spray and harsh weather. His body is robust and strong from decades of maritime labor, with calloused hands and the steady stance of one accustomed to life aboard ship.', '* Sogrlaf - Loyal crewman aboard the Northern Maiden * Lygrleid - Trusted crew member and longtime shipmate * Raven Rock Merchants - Business contacts who rely on his supply runs * Riften Dockworkers - Former colleagues from his early sailing days', 'Captain of the Northern Maiden, responsible for maintaining a vital transportation link between Skyrim and Solstheim. He manages both passenger transport and essential supply runs to Raven Rock, serving as one of the few reliable maritime connections between the two regions.', '* Expert ship navigation and seamanship * Skilled weather prediction and maritime navigation * Experienced cargo handler and trade negotiator * Proficient in basic ship maintenance and repairs * Knowledge of Solstheim''s coastal waters and safe harbors', 'Speaks with the gruff, direct manner of a seasoned sailor, employing maritime terminology and showing a preference for plain speech over flowery language. His tone carries the weight of experience, often tinged with wariness when discussing recent events on Solstheim.', '* Maintain a profitable shipping route despite declining conditions in Solstheim * Ensure the safety of his crew and vessel in increasingly dangerous waters * Eventually retire to Riften with enough savings to live comfortably * Preserve his reputation as a reliable captain despite his reservations about recent events');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gjuk', 'Gjuk is a gruff Nord warrior and loyal crew member of the Blood Horker pirates, serving under Captain Stig Salt-Plank''s command. A seasoned sailor with a taste for simple pleasures, he represents the archetypal Nordic pirate who finds contentment in mead, bread, and the camaraderie of his shipmates.', 'nord, warrior, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh northern coast, Gjuk likely spent his early years as a fisherman before turning to piracy under the Blood Horkers'' banner. His life at sea has hardened him into a capable warrior, though he maintains the traditional Nordic appreciation for festivity and strong drink that marks his cultural heritage.', 'Gjuk embodies the straightforward and rugged nature typical of Nord warriors, preferring direct action to subtle approaches. He''s fiercely loyal to his crew and captain, viewing them as a second family, and finds genuine joy in the simple pleasures of life aboard a pirate vessel. Despite his criminal lifestyle, he maintains a certain code of honor common among Nordic pirates.', 'A sturdy Nord with the weathered features and muscular build typical of a life at sea. His skin shows the effects of constant exposure to harsh elements, and his body bears the scars of numerous battles, marking him as an experienced warrior.', '* Captain Stig Salt-Plank - Respected leader and commander * Alding - Fellow crew member and drinking companion * Irlof - Trusted shipmate and fellow warrior * Blood Horkers - Criminal organization affiliation * East Empire Company - Enemy organization', 'Gjuk serves as a crew member aboard a Blood Horker pirate vessel, participating in raids against merchant ships and settlements along Skyrim''s northern coast. His duties likely include combat during raids, ship maintenance, and various tasks essential to maritime operations.', '* Experienced sailor with knowledge of seamanship and navigation * Proficient warrior skilled in close-quarters combat * Capable swimmer and survivor in harsh maritime conditions * Basic ship maintenance and repair abilities * Experienced raider with tactical combat experience', 'Gjuk speaks in a gruff, direct manner typical of Nord warriors, often using maritime slang and coarse language. His vocabulary is simple but effective, reflecting his practical nature and seafaring background.', '* Maintain his position and respect within the Blood Horkers crew * Accumulate wealth through successful piracy operations * Continue enjoying the freedom and adventure of the pirate''s life * Protect his crew members and maintain their collective success');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gloth', 'Gloth is a dedicated Nord farmhand who has found steady employment at Pelagia Farm, representing the backbone of Whiterun''s agricultural workforce. Despite his humble station, he maintains a reliable work ethic that keeps one of Whiterun''s primary food sources operational, though he remains trapped in a cycle of subsistence living.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born to a farming family somewhere in Whiterun Hold, Gloth likely spent his youth learning agricultural techniques and animal husbandry from his parents. After seeking his own path, he eventually found employment under Severio Pelagia, where the stability of the position outweighed its modest compensation. Years of farm work have shaped him into a dependable, if unambitious, laborer.', 'Gloth exhibits the stoic resilience typical of Nordic farmers, accepting his lot in life without complaint. He approaches his work with methodical dedication, finding satisfaction in routine tasks and showing particular care for the farm''s livestock. Though not particularly sociable, he maintains a cordial working relationship with his colleagues.', 'Gloth possesses the sturdy build common to Nord males, with callused hands and weather-worn features from years of outdoor labor. His physique shows the practical strength developed from daily farm work rather than martial training, with broad shoulders and a strong back suited to agricultural labor.', '* Severio Pelagia - Employer who provides steady work but rarely interacts directly * Nimriel - Fellow farm worker and daily companion * Whiterun Guards - Casual acquaintances who patrol near the farm * Local merchants - Basic trading relationships for necessities', 'As a farmhand at Pelagia Farm, Gloth''s primary responsibilities include tending to chickens, maintaining hay supplies, and performing general agricultural labor. His position, while essential to the farm''s operation, places him among Whiterun''s working poor, with barely enough income for basic necessities.', '* Experienced in animal husbandry, particularly with poultry care * Proficient in basic farming techniques and crop maintenance * Knowledge of agricultural seasons and weather patterns * Basic carpentry skills for farm equipment repair', 'Gloth speaks in simple, direct terms, using common Nordic vocabulary with a rural Whiterun accent. His speech patterns reflect his practical nature, focusing on immediate concerns and daily tasks rather than abstract concepts.', '* Maintain steady employment and avoid falling into destitution * Perhaps save enough septims to eventually own a small plot of land * Continue providing reliable service to secure his position at Pelagia Farm');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('glover_mallory', 'Glover Mallory is a skilled Breton blacksmith and former Thieves Guild member who has established himself as Raven Rock''s premier craftsman, specializing in Bonemold armor. While maintaining his legitimate business facade, he keeps his ties to the criminal underworld carefully hidden behind a locked basement door, representing the Guild''s sole presence on Solstheim.', 'breton, blacksmith, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Originally from Skyrim, Glover learned the art of smithing from a Dunmer named Vanryth, who taught him the unique techniques of Bonemold armor crafting. After his mentor''s departure, he chose to relocate to Solstheim to apply his specialized skills, seeing an opportunity in Raven Rock''s need for a capable smith. His criminal background as part of the Thieves Guild, shared with his brother Delvin, preceded his legitimate career, though he now prefers honest work.', 'Glover presents himself as an affable and hardworking craftsman, maintaining a friendly demeanor while keeping his past carefully guarded. He values both honest work and loyalty to old ties, demonstrated by his continued but passive association with the Thieves Guild. Though generally helpful and outgoing, he maintains certain boundaries, particularly regarding his secret basement and past life.', 'A sturdy Breton of middle age, Glover possesses the strong arms and calloused hands typical of a career blacksmith. His face shows the weathering of both his trade and Solstheim''s harsh climate, with features that bear a notable resemblance to his brother Delvin.', '* Delvin Mallory - Brother and fellow Thieves Guild member, maintaining distant but loyal family ties * Vanryth - Former mentor who taught him Bonemold crafting techniques * Thieves Guild - Maintains passive membership while avoiding active participation * Raven Rock Guards - Primary customers for his Bonemold armor work * Crescius Caerellius - Regular customer and acquaintance in Raven Rock', 'Glover serves as Raven Rock''s primary blacksmith, specializing in crafting and repairing Bonemold armor for the town guard. He maintains a successful smithy while secretly representing the Thieves Guild''s interests on Solstheim, though he rarely engages in guild activities.', '* Master-level smithing abilities, particularly with Bonemold armor crafting * Experienced in working with rare materials like Stalhrim * Skilled lockpick and stealth abilities from his Thieves Guild background * Proficient in basic combat with daggers and short blades * Knowledge of fence operations and black market trading', 'Glover speaks in a casual, friendly manner with a slight working-class accent, often using practical terminology related to his trade. His speech patterns reflect both his Breton heritage and years of living among the Dunmer of Solstheim.', '* Maintain his successful and legitimate blacksmithing business in Raven Rock * Preserve his connection to the Thieves Guild while avoiding active participation in their schemes * Keep his past life and secret basement contents hidden from the townsfolk * Continue developing his smithing skills, particularly with exotic materials');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('golldir', 'Golldir is a Nord warrior haunted by childhood trauma who guards his ancestral tomb while struggling to overcome his deep-seated fears of the place. Despite his inner turmoil, he shows great courage in seeking help to defend his family''s legacy from necromancers who would defile it.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into a Nord family with a long history of protecting their ancestral tomb, Golldir endured a traumatic childhood incident when his drunken father locked him in the family crypt for three days. He survived by eating the funeral offerings before being rescued by his Aunt Agna, who became his primary caregiver after his father''s abandonment. This experience left him with a debilitating fear of the tomb he''s destined to protect.', 'Golldir is a complex individual who struggles between his sense of duty and his deep-seated fears. Though initially appearing cowardly, he shows tremendous courage in facing his childhood trauma to protect his family''s legacy. He harbors guilt over his fear-induced failures but maintains a strong sense of honor and family duty.', 'Golldir is a sturdy Nord male with the characteristic robust build of his race. He bears the weather-worn features common to Skyrim''s natives, with a strong jaw and hardy constitution suited to the harsh climate.', '* Aunt Agna - His beloved caretaker who raised him after his father''s abandonment * Father (unnamed) - Estranged parent who traumatized him in childhood * Vals Veran - Nemesis who defiles his family tomb * Ancestral spirits - Dead relatives he''s sworn to protect * The Blades - Potential future allegiance if recruited', 'Golldir serves as the hereditary guardian of Hillgrund''s Tomb, tasked with protecting his ancestors'' remains from desecration. This role has been passed down through generations of his family, though his childhood trauma has complicated his ability to fulfill these duties.', '* Proficient warrior trained in traditional Nord combat techniques * Skilled with war axes and shields in the Nordic fighting style * Experienced in dealing with the undead and tomb defense * Knowledge of ancient Nordic burial customs and traditions', 'Golldir speaks with a typical Nordic accent and often references the Nine Divines, particularly Talos and Kyne. His speech patterns reveal both his inner turmoil and determination, frequently expressing both fear and resolve in the same breath.', '* Overcome his fear of the family tomb to properly honor his duty as guardian * Protect his ancestors'' remains from necromancers and other defilers * Avenge his Aunt Agna''s death and prevent further desecration of his family tomb * Find personal redemption for his past failures');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gonnar_oath-giver', 'Gonnar Oath-Giver is a fierce and dedicated Stormcloak commander stationed in Riften who embodies the nationalist ideals of the rebellion. A veteran warrior and tactical leader, he serves as both a military commander and a vocal advocate for Skyrim''s independence, representing the Stormcloaks'' presence in the Rift with unwavering conviction.', 'nord, warrior, rift, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh climate, Gonnar earned his surname through his reputation for keeping his word and demanding the same of others. He rose through the Stormcloak ranks through demonstrated leadership and unwavering loyalty to Ulfric''s cause, eventually earning his position as commander in the strategically important hold of the Rift.', 'Gonnar is a stern, principled warrior who holds traditional Nordic values in the highest regard. His fierce devotion to Skyrim''s independence and the worship of Talos drives his every action, while his strong sense of honor and dedication to oaths has earned him respect among both allies and enemies. He displays open contempt for those he views as betraying Skyrim, particularly Imperial sympathizers and the Thalmor.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with the weathered features typical of a veteran soldier who has spent years fighting in Skyrim''s harsh climate. His face bears several battle scars, and his body shows the physical conditioning of a warrior who maintains combat readiness at all times.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Deeply loyal commander who believes absolutely in Ulfric''s cause * Laila Law-Giver - Serves as military advisor while stationed in Riften * Maven Black-Briar - Tense relationship due to her Imperial connections * Fellow Stormcloak Officers - Maintains strong bonds of brotherhood with other commanders * Imperial Legion - Views them as betrayers of Skyrim and enemies to be defeated', 'Serves as a high-ranking commander in the Stormcloak army, responsible for military operations in the Rift region. His duties include managing troop movements, maintaining order in Stormcloak-controlled territories, and coordinating with local authorities while representing Ulfric''s interests.', '* Veteran warrior skilled in both one-handed weapons and archery * Tactical military commander with extensive battlefield experience * Natural leader capable of inspiring troops and maintaining discipline * Expert in Nordic combat traditions and warfare strategies * Proficient in survival skills necessary for extended campaigns in Skyrim''s wilderness', 'Speaks in a commanding, authoritative tone with a thick Nordic accent, often using martial metaphors and references to honor and tradition. His speech is direct and uncompromising, particularly when discussing matters of loyalty to Skyrim and the Stormcloak cause.', '* Drive the Imperial Legion from the Rift and secure the region for the Stormcloak cause * Restore the worship of Talos and eliminate Thalmor influence in Skyrim * Help establish Ulfric Stormcloak as the true High King of Skyrim * Preserve Nordic traditions and values for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gorm', 'Gorm is a steadfastly loyal Nord warrior who serves as housecarl to Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone of Morthal, struggling with his duty to protect a leader whose prophetic visions he increasingly distrusts. Despite his concerns about the Jarl''s mental state, he maintains unwavering dedication to both her personal safety and the welfare of Hjaalmarch.', 'nord, warrior, noble, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Morthal, Gorm earned his position as housecarl through demonstrated loyalty and martial prowess in service to Hjaalmarch. His years of dedicated service to Jarl Idgrod have given him unique insight into her prophetic abilities, though witnessing her increasingly frequent visions has caused him growing concern for both her wellbeing and ability to rule effectively.', 'Stern and protective, Gorm takes his duties as housecarl with utmost seriousness, often coming across as gruff or intimidating to visitors. While deeply loyal to Jarl Idgrod, he harbors private doubts about her prophetic visions, creating an internal conflict between his sworn duty and his concerns for Morthal''s future. Despite his tough exterior, he shows genuine care for both the Jarl''s family and Morthal''s wellbeing.', 'A sturdy Nord warrior with the weathered features typical of one who has spent years standing guard in Morthal''s harsh climate. His muscular build and battle-ready stance reflect his martial training and constant vigilance.', '* Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - His liege whom he loyally serves while harboring concerns about her mental state * Idgrod the Younger - The Jarl''s daughter whom he protects as part of his duties * Joric - The Jarl''s son whom he watches over with concern * Aslfur - The Jarl''s husband and steward with whom he maintains a professional working relationship * Captain Aldis - A contact in Solitude with whom he corresponds regarding Morthal''s security', 'As housecarl to Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone, Gorm serves as both personal bodyguard and head of security for Highmoon Hall. His responsibilities include protecting the Jarl and her family, maintaining order in the hall, and coordinating with other hold guards to ensure Morthal''s safety.', '* Experienced warrior trained in close combat with one-handed weapons * Skilled bodyguard with expertise in threat assessment and personal protection * Competent leader capable of coordinating guard duties and security measures * Trained in traditional Nordic combat techniques', 'Direct and intimidating, often using threats of violence to maintain order and respect for the Jarl. His speech reflects his no-nonsense attitude and military background, though he can speak diplomatically when necessary.', '* Ensure the safety and security of Jarl Idgrod and her family * Maintain order and stability in Highmoon Hall and Morthal * Find a way to address his concerns about the Jarl''s visions without betraying his oath * Protect Morthal''s interests during the civil war while maintaining his sworn duties');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gormlaith_golden-hilt', 'Gormlaith Golden-Hilt is a legendary Nord warrior-hero who fought alongside Felldir the Old and Hakon One-Eye in the first battle against Alduin during the Dragon War. A fearless dragonslayer who now resides in the Hall of Valor in Sovngarde, she represents the pinnacle of Nordic martial prowess and unwavering courage in the face of overwhelming odds.', 'nord, warrior, dragon', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born during the Merethic Era when dragons ruled over mortals, Gormlaith distinguished herself as one of the most accomplished dragonslayers of her time, personally claiming the lives of at least four dragons. She fought alongside her brother Hakon One-Eye and the elder mage Felldir the Old in humanity''s rebellion against dragon rule, culminating in their desperate gambit to use an Elder Scroll against Alduin at the Throat of the World. Though she fell in that battle, her warrior spirit earned her place in Sovngarde''s Hall of Valor.', 'Gormlaith embodies the archetypal Nordic warrior spirit - fierce, proud, and ever-eager for battle. She displays unwavering confidence in victory even against impossible odds, sometimes to the point of recklessness. Her enthusiasm for combat and glory occasionally puts her at odds with her more cautious companions, though she maintains absolute loyalty to her fellow warriors and causes she deems worthy.', 'A tall, muscular Nord woman with the bearing of a seasoned warrior. Her face bears the weathered features and battle scars of one who spent their life in combat, yet maintains a noble, striking appearance befitting a legendary hero. Her physical presence commands respect and attention, matching her reputation as one of Skyrim''s greatest warriors.', '* Hakon One-Eye - Beloved brother and fellow warrior against Alduin * Felldir the Old - Trusted companion and strategic advisor in the fight against the dragons * Other Ancient Nordic Heroes - Fellow residents in the Hall of Valor * Alduin - Sworn enemy and the ultimate target of her martial prowess * The Dragonborn - Respected ally in the final battle against the World-Eater', 'Gormlaith serves as one of Shor''s chosen warriors in the Hall of Valor, standing ready to fight for glory and honor in Sovngarde. In life, she was one of the most renowned dragonslayers of the Merethic Era, helping lead humanity''s rebellion against dragon rule.', '* Master of multiple Dragon Shouts including Dragonrend, Frost Breath, and Unrelenting Force * Expert swordswoman specializing in ancient Nordic combat techniques * Accomplished archer with precision in both ground and anti-dragon combat * Strategic battlefield commander with experience leading warriors against dragons * Masterful shield techniques combining both offense and defense', 'Gormlaith speaks with the bold, confident tone of a Nordic warrior-hero, favoring direct statements and battle cries. Her vocabulary reflects both her martial nature and her ancient origins, often using formal or archaic phrasings that emphasize honor and glory.', '* Continue serving with honor in Sovngarde''s Hall of Valor * Aid the Dragonborn in defeating Alduin once and for all * Inspire future generations of Nordic warriors through tales of her deeds * Maintain eternal vigilance against the threat of dragons');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gort', 'Gort is a seasoned Nord ferryman operating out of Windhelm''s busy port, known for his reliable maritime transport services along Skyrim''s northern coast. His years of experience navigating treacherous waters and knowledge of local maritime lore have made him a respected figure among travelers and merchants seeking safe passage.', 'nord, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Gort learned seafaring from his father who operated one of the city''s earliest ferry services. After serving briefly in the Windhelm guard in his youth, he inherited his father''s business and has spent decades mastering the dangerous northern waters, building a reputation for reliability despite the harsh conditions.', 'Gort is a pragmatic and straightforward individual who values honest work and fair payment for his services. While generally reserved, he possesses extensive knowledge of coastal settlements and maritime legends, which he shares with interested passengers. His cautious nature and respect for the sea''s dangers have kept him alive in his dangerous profession.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with weather-beaten features and calloused hands from years of rowing and rope work. His beard is grayed and neatly trimmed, and his posture reflects years of working on unstable surfaces, with strong shoulders and a balanced stance.', '* Thoring - Regular business contact at the Windpeak Inn in Dawnstar * Windhelm Dock Workers - Cooperative working relationship with fellow maritime workers * Local Merchants - Regular customers who rely on his ferry service * Sailors'' Guild - Respected member with good standing among fellow captains', 'Gort operates a vital ferry service from Windhelm''s dock, transporting passengers to various coastal destinations including Dawnstar, Solitude, and occasionally to more dangerous locations. He maintains his own vessel and negotiates fees based on distance and risk, serving as both captain and navigator.', '* Expert navigator familiar with Skyrim''s northern coastline and its hazards * Proficient warrior capable of defending his vessel with an iron war axe * Experienced sailor with knowledge of weather patterns and sea conditions * Strong physical conditioning from years of rowing and maritime work', 'Gort speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with the thick accent common to Windhelm natives. His speech is practical and business-oriented, though he occasionally shares maritime legends and local knowledge with interested passengers.', '* Maintain a profitable and reliable ferry service despite increasing dangers along the coast * Expand his business to include more regular routes to major ports * Save enough gold to eventually purchase a larger vessel for merchant shipping');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gregor', 'Gregor is a stalwart Nord warrior who serves as the personal housecarl to the Thane of the Pale, demonstrating unwavering loyalty and dedication to his duties. Despite his imposing presence as a warrior, he shows an unusual preference for wielding a greatsword alongside a shield, marking him as unique among his fellow housecarls.', 'nord, noble, warrior, pale, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh climate of the Pale, Gregor established himself as a capable warrior in service to the Hold, likely participating in numerous battles against bandits and other threats to Dawnstar''s security. His exceptional service and proven combat abilities eventually earned him the prestigious position of housecarl, appointed directly by Jarl Skald the Elder.', 'Gregor exhibits the archetypal Nord traits of loyalty, straightforwardness, and dedication to duty. He approaches his role as housecarl with utmost seriousness and pride, showing particular enthusiasm for protecting his Thane''s property and person. Though stoic in nature, he displays a warmth and eagerness to serve that sets him apart from other, more reserved housecarls.', 'Gregor possesses the robust build typical of Nord warriors, with broad shoulders and strong features hardened by the cold climate of the Pale. His physical appearance reflects years of combat experience, likely bearing several battle scars, and his stance suggests formal military training.', '* Jarl Skald the Elder - Direct superior who appointed him as housecarl * Thane of the Pale - Sworn to protect and serve with his life * Dawnstar Guard - Former colleagues from his time serving the hold * Jod - Professional relationship with Skald''s personal housecarl', 'As housecarl to the Thane of the Pale, Gregor serves as both a personal bodyguard and steward of Heljarchen Hall. His duties include protecting his Thane''s life and property, maintaining their homestead, and providing martial support during adventures and combat situations.', '* Exceptional two-handed weapon proficiency, particularly with greatswords * Skilled in heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Proficient in household management and property protection * Trained in Nordic combat traditions and battlefield tactics', 'Gregor speaks with the direct, respectful manner typical of Nord warriors, frequently addressing his Thane with appropriate honorifics. His speech patterns reflect his military background, being clear, concise, and formal without being overly rigid.', '* Serve and protect his Thane with unwavering loyalty and dedication * Maintain and defend Heljarchen Hall against all threats * Uphold the honored tradition of Nordic housecarls * Bring glory and honor to the Pale through faithful service');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('grelka', 'Grelka is a hardened Nord merchant who runs a successful armor stall in Riften''s marketplace, known for her expertise in light armor and her distinctly brusque manner with customers. Despite her harsh exterior, she is a skilled craftswoman and trainer who has been worn down by Skyrim''s harsh economic climate and ongoing civil war.', 'nord, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally from Falkreath, Grelka comes from a merchant family and learned her trade alongside her brothers Solaf and Bolund. She has traveled extensively throughout Skyrim as a traveling merchant before settling in Riften, where the challenging economic conditions and widespread corruption have left her jaded but determined to survive.', 'Grelka is cynical, direct, and unapologetically blunt in her interactions, having developed a thick skin from years of harsh merchant life. She maintains a pragmatic approach to business, caring little for social niceties or customer relations, instead focusing solely on making enough coin to eventually leave Skyrim.', 'A hardy Nord woman with the weathered features typical of someone who has spent years traveling Skyrim''s harsh roads. She maintains a strong, athletic build necessary for wearing and demonstrating light armor effectively.', '* Solaf - Brother who runs a general goods store in Falkreath * Bolund - Brother who works at the mill in Falkreath * Haelga - Landlord and owner of the bunkhouse where she resides * Bolli - Regular customer who sometimes complains about her merchandise * Thieves Guild - Maintains a disdainful attitude toward their presence in Riften', 'Grelka operates a market stall in Riften''s Grand Plaza, selling weapons, apparel, and various goods while also serving as an expert trainer in Light Armor. She maintains regular business hours and has established herself as one of the city''s primary armor merchants.', '* Expert-level knowledge and training ability in Light Armor * Experienced merchant with strong bargaining abilities * Proficient in armor maintenance and repair * Basic weapon knowledge for merchandising purposes * Survival skills developed from years of traveling across Skyrim', 'She speaks in a direct, often acidic tone, frequently using sarcasm and showing little patience for pleasantries. Her speech patterns reflect her no-nonsense attitude, often cutting conversations short to get straight to business.', '* Earn enough coin to leave Skyrim and its troubles behind * Maintain a profitable business despite Riften''s challenging economic climate * Avoid entanglement with the city''s criminal elements while staying in business * Eventually establish a more stable life away from war and dragons');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('grelod_the_kind', 'Grelod the Kind is the cruel and sadistic headmistress of Honorhall Orphanage in Riften, whose title is a bitter irony given her notorious abuse of the children in her care. Despite her advanced age, she maintains an iron grip of terror over the orphanage through psychological manipulation and physical abuse, having transformed what should be a sanctuary into a prison of despair.', 'imperial, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldgrumpy', '', 'Originally appointed as headmistress of Honorhall Orphanage decades ago, Grelod''s reign of cruelty has spanned generations of Riften''s orphans. Her past before taking charge of the orphanage remains mysterious, though rumors suggest she may have herself experienced abuse in her youth, perpetuating a cycle of cruelty. Years of unchecked authority and isolation have only served to amplify her sadistic tendencies.', 'Grelod is a sadistic tyrant who derives pleasure from emotionally and physically abusing the children in her care, displaying clear sociopathic tendencies with no capacity for empathy. She maintains control through fear, systematic abuse, and by crushing any hope of adoption or escape that her charges might harbor. Her cruelty appears to stem from a deep-seated need for power and control, possibly masking her own psychological trauma.', 'A withered Imperial woman in her late seventies, with a gaunt face marked by deep wrinkles and a perpetual scowl. Her thin frame belies surprising physical strength, and her sharp, predatory eyes reflect decades of inflicting cruelty on others.', '* Constance Michel - Assistant at the orphanage who disapproves of her methods but feels powerless to intervene * Orphaned Children - Victims of her abuse who live in constant fear of her * Riften Guards - Turn a blind eye to her activities, possibly due to bribes or political connections * Maven Black-Briar - Possible connection that helps maintain her position despite numerous complaints', 'Headmistress of Honorhall Orphanage in Riften, responsible for the care and placement of orphaned children. She actively prevents adoptions and runs the facility more like a prison than an orphanage, maintaining absolute control over every aspect of daily operations.', '* Expert in psychological manipulation and intimidation * Skilled at maintaining a facade of legitimacy to outside authorities * Proficient in administering calculated physical punishment without leaving obvious evidence * Experienced in institutional management and record-keeping', 'Her speech alternates between a falsely sweet, condescending tone when dealing with adults and a harsh, threatening manner with the children. She frequently employs cruel rhetoric and emotional manipulation, with a tendency to remind children of their worthlessness and hopeless situation.', '* Maintain absolute control over Honorhall Orphanage and its children * Prevent any adoptions to keep her power over the orphans intact * Preserve her position of authority in Riften despite her notorious reputation * Continue to operate without interference from local authorities or concerned citizens');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('greta', 'Greta is a grieving Nord woman in Solitude whose faith in Talos and family loyalty were tested by her brother Roggvir''s execution. A devoted mother and wife, she struggles to balance her religious convictions with the political reality of Imperial-controlled Solitude while maintaining her family''s stability in the wake of personal tragedy.', 'nord, priest, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Greta grew up in a traditional Nord family with strong ties to Talos worship. Her close relationship with her brother Roggvir was severed when he was executed for allowing Ulfric Stormcloak to escape after killing High King Torygg, an act that deeply affected her faith and emotional well-being while testing her loyalty to both family and beliefs.', 'Greta is a deeply religious and introspective woman who carries the weight of her brother''s death with quiet dignity. Though grief-stricken, she maintains her devotion to both family and faith, showing remarkable resilience in the face of adversity. She tends to be reserved with strangers but shows warmth to those who understand her situation.', 'A Nord woman of average height with the characteristic sturdy build of her race. Her face shows signs of recent emotional strain and sleepless nights, with visible worry lines around her eyes. Her movements are measured and deliberate, reflecting her careful and thoughtful nature.', '* Addvar - Loving husband and fishmonger whom she supports in running their business * Svari - Beloved daughter she strives to protect from political turmoil * Roggvir - Deceased brother whose memory she honors despite his controversial actions * Captain Aldis - Complicated relationship due to his role in her brother''s execution, though she acknowledges his understanding nature * Temple of the Divines clergy - Strained relationship due to her continued Talos worship', 'Greta assists her husband Addvar with his fish stall in the Solitude marketplace and takes full responsibility for running it if he dies. She manages their household and raises their daughter while maintaining their family''s position within Solitude''s merchant class.', '* Capable merchant with knowledge of local trade and commerce * Experienced in household management and child-rearing * Basic combat abilities for self-defense, particularly with daggers * Knowledge of traditional Nord customs and religious practices', 'Greta speaks in a quiet, subdued manner that reflects her ongoing mourning, often with undertones of melancholy. Her words are carefully chosen, especially when discussing sensitive topics like her brother or Talos worship.', '* Preserve her brother''s memory while protecting her family from similar fate * Maintain her faith in Talos despite Imperial prohibition * Ensure her daughter Svari grows up understanding Nord traditions while staying safe in Imperial-controlled Solitude * Keep her family''s business successful despite political tensions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('griefstricken_chef', 'A once-respected Nord chef turned vengeful warrior after experiencing a profound personal tragedy that drove him to seek the Dark Brotherhood''s services. Operating out of the Windpeak Inn in Dawnstar, he represents one of the rare individuals desperate enough to perform the Black Sacrament, marking a dark turn in an otherwise ordinary life.', 'nord, warrior, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally from the planned settlement of Heljarchen, he was forced to relocate to Dawnstar when the village''s development was abandoned. Previously renowned for his culinary expertise in traditional Nord cuisine, a devastating personal loss transformed him from a peaceful craftsman into a man consumed by thoughts of revenge, leading him to study the Dark Brotherhood''s summoning rituals.', 'Once jovial and proud of his craft, he now exhibits signs of severe emotional trauma and obsession with vengeance. His demeanor alternates between periods of numbed grief and intense emotional outbursts, particularly when discussing his contract. Despite his current state, glimpses of his former warmth occasionally surface when discussing cooking or his past life.', 'A sturdy Nord male of middle age, with the muscular build typical of his race though somewhat softened by years of kitchen work. His face bears the weathered features common to Skyrim''s harsh climate, with recent stress lines and dark circles beneath his eyes betraying his emotional turmoil.', '* Thoring - Current employer at the Windpeak Inn who provides him shelter * Dark Brotherhood - Desperate client seeking their services * Unknown Target - Subject of his contracted killing, identity varies * Former Heljarchen Community - Lost connections from his original home * Night Mother - Religious focus of his dark prayers and ritual', 'Formerly a respected chef in Heljarchen, now working as a cook at the Windpeak Inn in Dawnstar. His current position serves more as a cover for his true preoccupation with seeking revenge through the Dark Brotherhood''s services.', '* Exceptional culinary expertise, particularly in Nord cuisine * Basic combat training with daggers and kitchen implements * Knowledge of local ingredients and their properties * Ritual knowledge related to the Black Sacrament * Basic survival skills typical of Skyrim''s inhabitants', 'Speaks with a mix of traditional Nord dialect and culinary terminology, though now tinged with desperation and grief. His voice often breaks with emotion when discussing personal matters, while maintaining a eerily calm tone when speaking of revenge.', '* Complete his contract killing through the Dark Brotherhood * Achieve vengeance for his unnamed personal loss * Eventually find peace or purpose beyond his current grief * Potentially return to his former life as a respected chef if vengeance is achieved');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('grim_shieldmaiden', 'Grim Shieldmaiden is a skilled Nord blacksmith who operates the waterwheel-powered smithy in Markarth, known for her exceptional craftsmanship and brusque demeanor. Her dedication to her craft and solitary lifestyle have earned her both respect and notoriety in the city, though her past remains shrouded in mystery.', 'nord, blacksmith, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born into a family of traditional Nordic smiths, Grim learned the art of metalworking from an early age. After losing family members in the Great War, she relocated to Markarth, where the city''s Dwemer architecture and abundant silver mines provided opportunities to refine her craft in solitude.', 'Grim is a perfectionist who values efficiency and craftsmanship above social niceties, often coming across as cold or dismissive to those who interrupt her work. Her no-nonsense attitude and fierce independence stem from years of self-reliance, though beneath her harsh exterior lies a deep pride in her Nordic heritage and smithing traditions.', 'A tall, muscular Nord woman with calloused hands and strong arms shaped by years at the forge. Her face bears minor burn scars from metalworking, and her steel-gray eyes match the metals she works with daily.', '* Markarth Guard - Professional respect due to her quality weapon craftsmanship * Silver-Blood Family - Business association through smithing contracts * Local miners - Regular customers for tool maintenance and repairs * Blacksmiths Guild - Distant professional connections maintained through trade', 'As Markarth''s waterwheel smith, she specializes in crafting and maintaining weapons and armor, particularly those requiring precision work that can benefit from water-powered machinery. Her position is semi-independent, allowing her to accept both city contracts and private commissions.', '* Master-level smithing abilities, particularly in steel and silver working * Expertise in water-powered forge operation and maintenance * Accomplished warrior skilled with sword and shield * Knowledge of Dwemer metallurgy from working in Markarth * Physical strength and endurance from years of smithing work', 'Her speech is curt and utilitarian, with a thick Nordic accent and tendency to use smithing terminology. She speaks in short, direct sentences that get straight to the point, avoiding small talk or pleasantries.', '* Maintain her independence and reputation as one of Markarth''s premier smiths * Perfect her understanding of Dwemer metalworking techniques * Accumulate enough wealth to expand her smithing operation * Preserve traditional Nordic smithing methods while incorporating modern innovations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('grisvar_the_unlucky', 'Grisvar the Unlucky is a Nord thief whose string of misfortunes led to his life imprisonment in Cidhna Mine, Markarth''s notorious prison mine. His desperate addiction to skooma and reputation for bad luck have made him a pitiful figure among his fellow inmates, willing to trade valuable contraband for his next fix.', 'nord, thief, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born to a modest farming family near Markarth, Grisvar turned to thievery in his youth after a series of crop failures left his family destitute. His criminal career was marked by consistent failures and near-captures, earning him his unfortunate moniker. After numerous botched heists and close calls, his luck finally ran out when he was caught attempting to steal from the Treasury House in Markarth.', 'Grisvar is a desperate and cunning individual whose addiction to skooma has eroded his former pride and dignity. Despite his circumstances, he maintains a survivor''s instinct and understands the delicate social dynamics of prison life. His pleading demeanor masks a shrewd mind that''s always looking for opportunities to trade and negotiate for his next skooma fix.', 'A gaunt Nord male showing the physical deterioration typical of long-term skooma addiction, with sunken eyes and yellowed skin. His once-sturdy Nordic frame has become thin and wiry from years of prison labor and drug use.', '* Madanach - Fearful relationship with the King in Rags, who may order his death * Braig - Fellow prisoner with whom he maintains cautious communication * Prison Guards - Antagonistic yet occasionally cooperative when seeking contraband * Skooma Dealers - Maintains whatever connections possible to feed his addiction', 'Grisvar serves as a prisoner-miner in Cidhna Mine, forced to work the silver veins for the Silver-Blood family. Prior to his imprisonment, he worked as a petty thief and burglar throughout the Reach.', '* Experienced in lockpicking and stealth, though skills have deteriorated due to addiction * Knowledgeable about Cidhna Mine''s contraband trading networks * Skilled at bartering and negotiating within prison economy * Basic mining abilities developed during imprisonment', 'Speaks with a pleading, desperate tone typical of addicts, often punctuating his sentences with nervous laughter or fearful stammering. His vocabulary reveals glimpses of a once-sharper mind now clouded by skooma addiction.', '* Secure a steady supply of skooma to feed his addiction * Survive the harsh conditions of Cidhna Mine * Eventually earn release or escape from prison, though this seems increasingly unlikely * Overcome his skooma addiction, though he lacks the willpower to seriously pursue this');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('grogmar_gro-burzag', 'Grogmar Gro-Burzag is a skilled Orcish miner who has carved out a respectable life for himself in the small village of Shor''s Stone. Known throughout the region for his exceptional ability to smell out valuable ore deposits, he represents a unique blend of traditional Orcish strength and specialized mining expertise that has earned him both a comfortable living and the respect of his fellow villagers.', 'orc, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into a traditional Orcish stronghold, Grogmar chose to leave the warrior''s path expected of most male Orcs to pursue his passion for mining after discovering his unique talent for detecting ore. His journey led him to various mining operations across Skyrim before finally settling in Shor''s Stone, where he found both purpose and community. Years of working in dangerous mines have hardened him physically and mentally, while teaching him the value of cooperation over the typical Orcish preference for isolation.', 'Despite his intimidating Orcish heritage, Grogmar displays an unusually sociable nature for his kind, fostering friendly rivalries and engaging in good-natured competition with his fellow miners. He takes immense pride in his mining abilities and expertise, often using these as measuring sticks for his self-worth rather than the traditional Orcish values of combat prowess. While generally good-natured, he maintains high standards for work ethic and has little patience for laziness or incompetence.', 'Grogmar possesses the typical robust build of an Orc, with pronounced muscles developed through years of mining work. His green skin bears numerous scars and calluses from mining accidents, while his tusks show slight wear from years of gritting them during particularly challenging excavations. His hands are exceptionally large and strong, even by Orcish standards, adapted to the daily rigors of mining work.', '* Odfel - Close friend and friendly rival in mining expertise, sharing living quarters and daily life * Filnjar - Respected employer and leader of Shor''s Stone * Other miners - Maintains cordial working relationships built on mutual respect * Traveling merchants - Regular business contacts for selling ore and purchasing supplies', 'Grogmar serves as one of the primary miners in Redbelly Mine, specializing in iron ore extraction. His exceptional sense of smell for ore makes him particularly valuable to the mining operation, and he supplements his income by purchasing ore from travelers and managing small-scale ore trading.', '* Expert-level mining ability with specialized knowledge of iron ore extraction * Extraordinary sense of smell for detecting mineral deposits * Considerable physical strength and stamina from years of mining work * Basic trading and bartering skills developed through ore transactions * Fundamental knowledge of mine safety and structural integrity', 'Grogmar speaks in a gruff but straightforward manner, often punctuating his statements with mining-related metaphors and references to his work. His speech patterns reflect his pride in his profession, frequently incorporating technical mining terminology while maintaining the direct, no-nonsense approach typical of Orcs.', '* Maintain and enhance Redbelly Mine''s productivity and safety * Prove himself as the most skilled miner in The Rift region * Establish a more efficient ore trading network with traveling merchants * Eventually save enough money to purchase his own mine or establish a mining operation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('grosta', 'Grosta is a resilient Nord woman who runs Heartwood Mill following her husband''s mysterious disappearance, displaying both strength and hidden vulnerability as she maintains the family business. Despite her hardened exterior, she maintains a pragmatic approach to survival while harboring deep emotional wounds from her husband''s presumed betrayal.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally settling at Heartwood Mill with her husband Leifnarr and son Gralnach, Grosta helped build a modest but successful lumber operation in Skyrim''s wilderness. Her life took a dramatic turn when Leifnarr disappeared during a trading expedition to Broken Helm Hollow, leaving her to manage the mill alone while caring for their son. The experience of sudden abandonment transformed her from a trusting spouse into a cynical and guarded individual.', 'Grosta presents a stoic and matter-of-fact demeanor, masking her emotional pain with bluntness and cynicism, particularly regarding men. Though outwardly bitter, she maintains a strong sense of responsibility and work ethic, continuing to operate the mill despite challenging circumstances. Her interactions reveal a complex character who balances practical business sense with deep-seated trust issues.', 'A hardy Nord woman with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. Her face shows the weathering effects of working outdoors, with calloused hands and strong arms from years of lumber work. Her overall appearance reflects the demanding nature of her profession while maintaining the proud bearing characteristic of Nord women.', '* Leifnarr - Missing husband whom she initially believes abandoned her for another woman * Gralnach - Her son who helps at the mill * Local farmers - Business connections through lumber trade * Traders from Broken Helm Hollow - Suspicious of their role in her husband''s disappearance', 'Grosta serves as both owner and primary operator of Heartwood Mill, managing all aspects of the lumber business from cutting trees to selling finished wood products. She maintains the mill''s operations while training her son in the family trade, though she struggles to keep the business profitable without her husband''s help.', '* Experienced lumberjack capable of felling and processing trees * Proficient with war axe for both logging and self-defense * Basic business management and trading abilities * Survival skills necessary for living in Skyrim''s wilderness', 'Direct and unembellished speech pattern typical of working-class Nords, often tinged with bitterness when discussing personal matters. She tends to be blunt and occasionally confrontational, particularly when expressing her views about men.', '* Keep Heartwood Mill operational despite financial difficulties * Uncover the truth about her husband''s disappearance * Ensure her son''s future by maintaining the family business * Achieve financial stability before the mill becomes unsustainable');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('guardian_saerek', 'Guardian Saerek is an ancient and formidable draugr warrior who serves as one of the principal defenders of Ragnvald Crypts. Once a respected Nord warrior trusted with protecting sacred treasures, he now exists as an undead sentinel, wielding both martial prowess and the power of dragon shouts to eliminate any who dare intrude upon his eternal watch.', 'nord, warrior', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'In life, Saerek was a highly-regarded Nord warrior who earned the honor of being appointed as one of Ragnvald''s elite guardians during the Merethic Era or early First Era. He was likely one of several warriors who underwent a ritual of eternal service, willingly accepting undeath to continue their sacred duty of protecting the crypts and its treasures. His dedication was so absolute that even death could not end his vigilant watch.', 'Saerek exhibits the single-minded focus and unwavering dedication typical of high-ranking draugr, completely devoted to his duty as guardian. Unlike lesser draugr who mindlessly attack, he displays tactical intelligence in combat and a fierce determination that speaks to his warrior''s spirit. Though now silent, his actions reveal a proud and honorable nature that has persisted even in undeath.', 'Saerek stands taller than the average draugr, with a muscular, well-preserved corpse that reflects his warrior status in life. His desiccated flesh clings tightly to his frame, and his eyes burn with an intense blue ethereal fire that marks him as a powerful draugr lord. Ancient Nordic tattoos and battle scars are still visible on his withered skin.', '* Otar the Mad - Fellow guardian of Ragnvald, likely served alongside him in life * Other Ragnvald Draugr - Commands authority over lesser undead in the crypt * Ancient Nord Priests - Likely served under their authority when alive * Adventurers and Tomb Raiders - Views all as enemies to be eliminated without mercy', 'As one of Ragnvald''s principal guardians, Saerek''s eternal duty is to protect the crypts and its sacred treasures from desecration. His position suggests he holds a rank of significant importance among the draugr hierarchy, second perhaps only to the dragon priests in authority within the tomb''s defensive structure.', '* Master-level prowess with two-handed weapons, particularly ancient Nordic weapons * Command of powerful dragon shouts including Disarm and Unrelenting Force * Enhanced strength and endurance typical of high-ranking draugr * Tactical combat expertise from his mortal life as a warrior * Natural resistance to frost and poison due to his undead nature', 'Guardian Saerek no longer engages in verbal communication, though he may emit guttural growls and ancient Nordic battle cries during combat. When using dragon shouts, his voice carries the powerful resonance characteristic of those who truly understand the Thu''um.', '* Maintain eternal vigilance over Ragnvald Crypts and its treasures * Eliminate any intruders who dare to violate the sacred tomb * Preserve the ancient Nordic traditions and sanctity of the burial grounds * Continue serving with honor in death as he did in life');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gul', 'Gul is a dedicated Orc miner at Mor Khazgur stronghold who embodies the Orcish values of hard work, duty, and devotion to Malacath. Her tireless work ethic and expertise in mining orichalcum ore make her an essential member of the stronghold''s workforce, contributing directly to her community''s strength and prosperity.', 'orc, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Mor Khazgur, Gul learned the art of mining from an early age, as is tradition among the Orsimer. She has spent decades honing her craft in the orichalcum mines, having likely inherited her position from previous generations of miners who served the stronghold. Her unwavering dedication to her work has earned her a respected position within the stronghold''s hierarchy.', 'Gul is stoic, focused, and deeply religious, viewing her mining work as a sacred duty blessed by Malacath. She shows little patience for idle conversation or interruptions, preferring to concentrate on her tasks with single-minded determination. Her pride in her work manifests not through boasting, but through quiet competence and religious devotion.', 'Gul possesses the characteristic robust build of an Orc female, with powerful arms and shoulders developed through years of mining work. Her green-tinted skin bears the weathered marks of countless hours spent in the mines, and her prominent tusks and strong jaw display typical Orsimer features.', '* Ghamorz - Fellow miner and daily work companion * Olur - Mining colleague who shares her dedication to the craft * Chief Larak - Stronghold leader whom she serves through her work * Malacath - Revered deity to whom she dedicates her labor', 'Gul serves as one of the primary miners in Mor Khazgur''s orichalcum mine, working alongside Ghamorz and Olur to extract valuable ore for the stronghold. Her role is vital to the community''s economy and survival, as orichalcum is essential for crafting traditional Orcish weapons and armor.', '* Expert mining techniques and ore identification * Physical endurance and strength from years of manual labor * Basic combat abilities typical of Orsimer warriors * Knowledge of orichalcum processing and mineral assessment', 'Gul speaks in terse, direct statements, often dismissing conversation with references to her work or Malacath''s will. Her tone is gruff and matter-of-fact, reflecting her no-nonsense approach to life.', '* Continue serving her stronghold through diligent mining work * Honor Malacath through dedication to her craft * Maintain the prosperity of Mor Khazgur through resource extraction * Pass on mining knowledge to future generations of the stronghold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gularzob', 'Gularzob is an Orcish warrior who rises from a humble guard to become the divinely-appointed chieftain of Largashbur after Malacath''s intervention. Though initially uncertain of his calling, he embraces his new role with determination and honor, dedicated to leading his stronghold according to ancient Orcish traditions and preventing the failures of his predecessor.', 'orc, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Originally serving as a guard in Largashbur, Gularzob witnessed the stronghold''s decline under Chieftain Yamarz''s weak leadership and the curse that plagued their home. After Yamarz''s betrayal and death, Malacath personally selected Gularzob to lead the stronghold, seeing in him the qualities of a true Orcish leader despite his modest position.', 'Gularzob is humble yet determined, showing wisdom in acknowledging his own limitations while remaining committed to growth as a leader. He values loyalty and tradition deeply, taking his responsibilities seriously and actively seeking counsel from wise members of his tribe. His sense of honor and dedication to the Orc code guides his decisions and actions.', 'Gularzob possesses the imposing physicality typical of male Orcs, with a muscular build hardened by years of guard duty. His green-tinted skin bears the scars of combat, and his prominent tusks and strong jaw display classic Orsimer features.', '* Atub - Trusted advisor and wise woman of Largashbur whose counsel he greatly values * Malacath - Daedric Prince who chose him as chieftain and to whom he owes ultimate loyalty * Former Chieftain Yamarz - Failed predecessor whose mistakes he strives not to repeat * Largashbur Tribe Members - Subjects under his protection and leadership', 'As Chieftain of Largashbur, Gularzob oversees all aspects of stronghold life, from security to resource management. He maintains traditional patrol duties despite his elevated status, demonstrating his hands-on leadership style and commitment to the stronghold''s protection.', '* Proficient warrior trained in traditional Orcish combat techniques * Experienced guard with keen defensive tactical knowledge * Leadership abilities recognized by Malacath himself * Understanding of Orcish traditions and tribal governance', 'Gularzob speaks with the direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Orcs, but tempers his words with humility regarding his position. His speech reflects both traditional Orcish values and his personal uncertainty about leadership.', '* Prove himself worthy of Malacath''s choice by becoming a strong and effective leader * Restore Largashbur to prosperity after lifting of the curse * Maintain the traditions and honor of the Orcish people * Prevent any future betrayals or failures like those of Yamarz');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gulum-ei', 'Gulum-Ei is a duplicitous Argonian dock worker who serves as both an East Empire Company employee and a covert informant for the Thieves Guild, though his loyalty shifts with whoever offers the better deal. His position as a warehouse operator allows him to facilitate smuggling operations while maintaining a facade of legitimate business, making him a valuable albeit unreliable asset in Solitude''s criminal underworld.', 'argonian, peasant, haafingar, legion, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally from Black Marsh, Gulum-Ei moved to Skyrim seeking opportunities in maritime trade, eventually securing a position with the East Empire Company in Solitude. He established connections with the Thieves Guild early in his career, using his warehouse access to profit from both legitimate and illegal merchandise. His siblings Deeja and Jaree-Ra followed him to Skyrim, though their relationship has grown complicated due to competing criminal interests.', 'Gulum-Ei is a cautious and self-serving individual who prioritizes personal profit above all else, including loyalty to his associates. Though not particularly skilled at deception, he maintains his position through careful manipulation of information and access to valuable resources. He presents a dismissive and aloof exterior to strangers while remaining calculating and opportunistic in his dealings.', 'A mature Argonian male with grayish-green scales and dark ridges along his head. His posture is slightly hunched from years of warehouse work, and his eyes have the characteristic amber glow common to his race. His movements are deliberate and measured, betraying his cautious nature.', '* East Empire Company - Employer and primary target of his subtle theft * Thieves Guild - Former close associate turned reluctant informant * Mercer Frey - Distrustful relationship due to recent betrayal * Deeja and Jaree-Ra - Siblings with whom he maintains complex criminal ties * Various Solitude merchants - Business contacts who may or may not know of his illegal activities', 'Gulum-Ei officially works as a warehouse operator for the East Empire Company, managing inventory and supervising dock operations. Unofficially, he serves as a fence and informant, using his position to facilitate the movement of stolen goods and gather valuable information about shipping schedules and cargo manifests.', '* Expert in warehouse management and inventory systems * Proficient in basic combat with daggers and frost magic * Skilled in identifying valuable merchandise and assessing market prices * Adept at maintaining multiple false identities and covers * Experienced smuggler with knowledge of various trade routes', 'He speaks in short, dismissive sentences when dealing with strangers, but becomes more verbose and accommodating when potential profit is involved. His tone is generally curt and businesslike, with occasional nervous undertones when pressed about his illegal activities.', '* Maintain his position within the East Empire Company while maximizing personal profit * Rebuild his relationship with the Thieves Guild on more favorable terms * Protect himself from potential repercussions of his various betrayals * Expand his network of profitable criminal connections while minimizing risk');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gunding', 'Gunding is a determined Nord miner at Whistling Mine who embodies the Nordic spirit of perseverance despite challenging circumstances. Despite the mine''s meager yields, he maintains an unwavering optimism about striking it rich, often working long hours in pursuit of his dreams of finding valuable deposits beyond the common iron ore.', 'nord, peasant, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born to a working-class family in Skyrim, Gunding learned the mining trade from an early age, likely following in his father''s footsteps. He eventually found his way to Whistling Mine, attracted by rumors of untapped mineral wealth in the area, though the reality has proven less profitable than hoped. Despite years of minimal success, he continues to invest his time and energy into the mine, refusing to abandon his dreams of discovery.', 'Gunding is an eternal optimist who maintains his cheerful disposition even in the face of limited success, often encouraging himself and others with dreams of striking it rich. His determination borders on self-deception, as he pushes himself to exhaustion while clinging to the belief that the next swing of his pickaxe could reveal untold riches. Despite the harsh reality of his situation, he maintains a friendly and welcoming demeanor to all visitors.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. Years of mining have left his hands calloused and his face weathered, though his eyes still maintain a bright, hopeful gleam. His posture, despite long hours of work, remains straight and proud in true Nordic fashion.', '* Fellow Miners - Maintains cordial working relationships with others at Whistling Mine * Local Merchants - Regular business contacts for selling ore and purchasing supplies * Traveling Traders - Occasional interactions when selling minerals and seeking news of other mining operations', 'Gunding works as a full-time miner at Whistling Mine, focusing primarily on extracting iron ore but constantly searching for more valuable minerals. He takes on all aspects of the mining operation, from excavation to basic ore processing, and likely handles some of the business transactions with local merchants.', '* Experienced in mining techniques and ore identification * Proficient with mining tools and basic weapons * Knowledge of mineral deposits and their potential value * Physical endurance and strength from years of mining work * Basic trading and bartering abilities', 'Speaks in a casual, friendly manner with a distinct Nordic accent, often peppering his conversation with optimistic statements about future prospects. His vocabulary is simple but practical, reflecting his working-class background and focused primarily on mining-related topics.', '* Strike a rich vein of precious metals or gems in Whistling Mine * Prove to himself and others that his dedication to the mine will eventually pay off * Save enough money to potentially expand mining operations or invest in better equipment * Find success and recognition as a prosperous miner in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gunjar', 'Gunjar was a devoted Stormcloak soldier who faced execution at Helgen alongside Ralof and other rebels. A proud Nord warrior who embodied the fighting spirit of his people, his life was cut short during the chaos of Alduin''s attack despite managing to initially escape the execution block.', 'nord, whiterun, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Gunjar likely grew up in one of the Old Holds where Nordic traditions and resistance to Imperial rule ran strong. He joined the Stormcloak rebellion early in the civil war, fighting alongside his close friend Ralof in numerous battles before their capture by Imperial forces near the Pale Pass.', 'Gunjar exemplified the fierce loyalty and warrior spirit characteristic of Nordic soldiers, showing unwavering dedication to the Stormcloak cause even in the face of death. His close friendship with Ralof suggests he valued brotherhood and camaraderie, while his willingness to face execution rather than renounce his beliefs demonstrates his strong principles and courage.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the muscular build typical of Skyrim''s warriors. Like many of his kinsmen, he likely possessed the fair complexion and strong features common among Nords, hardened by combat and Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Ralof - Close friend and brother-in-arms in the Stormcloak rebellion * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respected leader and commander he served under * Imperial Legion - Enemies who captured and sentenced him to death * Fellow Stormcloak Soldiers - Brothers and sisters in arms who shared his cause', 'Gunjar served as a soldier in the Stormcloak rebellion, fighting to free Skyrim from Imperial control. His position likely involved combat duties, patrol assignments, and participating in military operations against Imperial forces.', '* Proficient in traditional Nord warfare, especially with war axes and other Nordic weapons * Experienced in combat tactics used by Stormcloak rebels * Skilled in surviving Skyrim''s harsh environment during military campaigns * Basic armor maintenance and battlefield first aid knowledge', 'Speaks with a thick Nordic accent and uses direct, military-style communication. His tone is gruff and determined, reflecting his soldier''s discipline and Nord heritage.', '* Fight for Skyrim''s independence from the Empire * Serve the Stormcloak cause with honor and dedication * Help establish a free Skyrim under traditional Nord rule * Die with honor to reach Sovngarde');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gunmar', 'Gunmar is a skilled Nord blacksmith and master-level smithing trainer who becomes a vital member of the Dawnguard vampire hunters. A gruff but capable warrior-craftsman, he combines his expertise in metalworking with a fierce dedication to protecting Skyrim''s people from supernatural threats.', 'nord, blacksmith, rift, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Before joining the Dawnguard, Gunmar lived as a wandering blacksmith and monster hunter, tracking and eliminating dangerous creatures that threatened settlements across Skyrim. His experiences dealing with various supernatural threats, particularly the loss of loved ones to vampire attacks, led him to develop a deep hatred for vampires and eventually join forces with Isran''s Dawnguard.', 'Gunmar is a pragmatic and no-nonsense individual who values direct action over lengthy discussion. Though gruff and sometimes brusque in his interactions, he demonstrates unwavering loyalty to the Dawnguard''s cause and genuine concern for protecting innocent civilians. His practical mindset and years of experience have made him somewhat cynical, but he maintains a strong sense of duty and honor.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with a muscular build developed through years of smithing and combat. His weather-beaten face bears several small scars from his monster-hunting days, and his hands are calloused from working the forge. His overall appearance reflects years of outdoor living and hard work.', '* Isran - Respected leader of the Dawnguard, though their personalities sometimes clash * Sorine Jurard - Fellow Dawnguard specialist, shares mutual respect for technical expertise * Florentius Baenius - Tolerates his eccentric behavior for the sake of the Dawnguard''s mission * Local settlements - Maintains connections with villages he''s helped by eliminating dangerous wildlife', 'Gunmar serves as the Dawnguard''s master blacksmith and monster handler, crafting weapons and armor while also training armored trolls for combat. He additionally takes on the role of field commander for various vampire-hunting missions, coordinating strikes against vampire lairs and training new recruits in combat tactics.', '* Master-level blacksmithing abilities, specializing in anti-vampire weapons and armor * Expert monster handler, particularly skilled with training combat trolls * Accomplished tracker and hunter with extensive wilderness survival knowledge * Proficient warrior specialized in close-quarters combat * Experienced monster hunter with detailed knowledge of various supernatural threats', 'Gunmar speaks in a deep, gravelly voice with the typical Nordic accent, favoring direct and practical language. He tends to be terse and to-the-point, often dispensing with pleasantries in favor of getting straight to business.', '* Eradicate vampire threats throughout Skyrim to protect innocent civilians * Expand and strengthen the Dawnguard''s capabilities through improved equipment and trained war-beasts * Perfect his craft of creating specialized anti-vampire weapons and armor * Establish a network of monster hunters to better protect Skyrim''s settlements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gunnar_stone-eye', 'Gunnar Stone-Eye is a weathered Nord miner and respected elder of Helgen who earned his nickname from a mining accident that left him with a distinctive clouded eye. Despite his age, he remains a pillar of strength in the community, known for his protective nature and willingness to put himself in harm''s way to defend others, as demonstrated during Alduin''s attack.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and raised in the shadow of the Jerall Mountains, Gunnar spent over four decades working the mines near Helgen, surviving numerous cave-ins and accidents including the one that cost him partial vision. His experience with tragedy and hardship, combined with his natural Nord sense of honor, shaped him into an unofficial guardian of the community, particularly its younger members.', 'Gunnar embodies the stoic resilience typical of Nord elders, maintaining a gruff exterior that belies his deeply protective nature. He approaches life with pragmatic wisdom earned through years of hard work and survival, holding fast to traditional Nord values of honor, duty, and community protection. His experiences have left him with a particular soft spot for children, whom he views as the future of Skyrim.', 'A tall, broad-shouldered Nord whose once-powerful frame still carries impressive strength despite his advanced age. His most distinctive feature is his clouded right eye, surrounded by scarring from an old mining accident, while his face is deeply lined and weathered from decades of outdoor work. His thick grey hair and beard show the last traces of their original blonde color.', '* Haming - Young boy of Helgen whom he protects during Alduin''s attack * Torolf - Haming''s father, fellow townsman he respects * Helgen Guards - Maintains good working relationship with local security * Local Miners - Serves as an informal leader and mentor to younger workers * Helgen Townspeople - Respected elder figure in the community', 'Gunnar works as a senior miner in the nearby mines, though his role has evolved to become more supervisory due to his age and experience. He serves as an informal mentor to younger miners and occasional advisor to town authorities on matters of mining safety and civil protection.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of local geology and mining safety * Capable warrior with traditional Nord combat training * Natural leader with crisis management abilities * Skilled storyteller, particularly of old Nord tales and mining legends * Basic first aid knowledge from years of mining accidents', 'Speaks in a deep, gravelly voice with a thick Nordic accent, favoring direct, practical language with occasional traditional Nord sayings. His tone carries the weight of authority earned through experience, though it softens notably when addressing children.', '* Ensure the safety and survival of Helgen''s residents, particularly its youth * Pass on traditional Nord values and mining knowledge to the next generation * Maintain his role as a community protector despite his advancing age * Help rebuild Helgen''s community after any disasters or hardships');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('guthrum', 'Guthrum is a veteran Nord ranger and lifelong sailor who has made the Sea Squall in Dawnstar his permanent home in his twilight years. Despite his advanced age, he remains a capable warrior and experienced seaman whose deep connection to maritime life has become an inseparable part of his identity.', 'nord, sailor, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s northern coast, Guthrum spent decades sailing both rivers and seas, likely serving on various vessels before settling in Dawnstar. His extensive maritime experience spans both merchant vessels and possibly combat operations, given his ranger training and warrior capabilities. His decision to remain aboard the permanently docked Sea Squall suggests a deep-seated need to maintain his connection to seafaring life even in his elder years.', 'Guthrum is a steadfast and dedicated sailor who finds purpose and contentment in maintaining his maritime lifestyle, even when permanently docked. He displays patience and wisdom in his mentorship of less experienced sailors like Captain Wayfinder, while maintaining a practical and straightforward approach to life. His unwavering dedication to seafaring life suggests both stubbornness and deep personal conviction.', 'Guthrum is an elderly Nord with the weathered features and sturdy build typical of longtime sailors. His skin shows the effects of decades of exposure to sea winds and sun, with deep creases around his eyes from years of squinting at the horizon. Despite his advanced age, he maintains the physical capability and bearing of an experienced warrior.', '* Captain Wayfinder - Respects his position while acknowledging his inexperience * Sea Squall Crew - Fellow sailors who share his maritime lifestyle * Dawnstar Citizens - Maintains casual acquaintances with locals who frequent the docks', 'Guthrum serves as a senior crew member aboard the Sea Squall, performing maintenance duties and likely serving as an unofficial advisor given his extensive experience. His role combines the practical aspects of ship maintenance with the traditional duties of a ranger, making him a valuable asset despite the vessel''s stationary status.', '* Expert maritime navigation and seafaring * Proficient warrior trained in combat with axes * Experienced ranger with survival skills * Ship maintenance and deck work specialist * Weather prediction and sea condition assessment', 'Guthrum speaks in a gruff, seasoned manner with the typical Nordic accent, frequently using nautical terminology and maritime metaphors. His speech patterns reflect his years at sea, often direct and practical, while conveying wisdom earned through experience.', '* Maintain his connection to maritime life until his final days * Pass on his seafaring knowledge to younger sailors * Continue serving as a valuable crew member despite his advanced age * Preserve the traditions and practices of proper seamanship');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gwendolyn', 'Gwendolyn is a dedicated Nord farmer who maintains Battle-Born Farm, one of Whiterun''s primary agricultural centers. Her solitary lifestyle and unwavering work ethic make her an essential yet understated contributor to Whiterun''s food supply, representing the backbone of Nordic agricultural tradition.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born into a farming family, Gwendolyn likely inherited or was appointed to manage Battle-Born Farm due to her expertise in agriculture and connection to the influential Battle-Born clan. Her deep understanding of Whiterun''s soil and climate conditions suggests she has spent most of her life in the region, learning the intricacies of crop management and seasonal farming patterns unique to Skyrim''s harsh environment.', 'Gwendolyn embodies the Nordic values of hard work and self-reliance, approaching her duties with quiet determination and practical wisdom. Her solitary nature and dedication to routine suggest someone who finds fulfillment in honest labor rather than social interactions, though she maintains necessary professional relationships to ensure the farm''s success.', 'As a Nord who spends long hours working outdoors, Gwendolyn has a sturdy, weather-worn physique typical of her race. Her features show the effects of constant exposure to the elements, with calloused hands and sun-weathered skin reflecting years of agricultural labor.', '* Battle-Born Clan - Employers and owners of the farm she manages * Severio Pelagia - Fellow farmer and occasional trading partner * Whiterun merchants - Professional contacts for selling crops and purchasing supplies * Local farmhands - Occasional working relationships during harvest seasons', 'Gwendolyn serves as the primary caretaker of Battle-Born Farm, responsible for all aspects of crop management from planting to harvest. Her position requires extensive knowledge of agricultural techniques and crop timing, as well as the ability to maintain consistent food production for Whiterun''s population.', '* Expert knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Proficient in tool maintenance and basic equipment repair * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Understanding of weather patterns and seasonal farming cycles * Skilled in crop rotation and soil management', 'She speaks in a direct, practical manner with a thick Nordic accent, often focusing on agricultural matters and daily concerns. Her vocabulary reflects her farming expertise, frequently incorporating technical terms related to cultivation and weather patterns.', '* Maintain the productivity and reputation of Battle-Born Farm * Ensure consistent crop yields to support Whiterun''s food supply * Preserve and pass on traditional Nordic farming techniques * Potentially expand the farm''s operations when resources allow');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gwilin', 'Gwilin is a cheerful Wood Elf sawmill worker in Ivarstead who maintains an infectiously positive outlook despite challenging working conditions. As Temba Wide-Arm''s apprentice, he represents a rare example of a Bosmer who has adapted to life outside the forests of Valenwood, finding contentment in honest labor and simple pleasures.', 'woodelf, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born to Bosmer parents who likely migrated from Valenwood, Gwilin was raised with strong philosophical teachings from his father about finding joy in life''s simple pleasures. He eventually made his way to Skyrim and settled in Ivarstead, where he found purpose working at the sawmill, breaking from the typical Wood Elf traditions of forest-dwelling and strict carnivorous diets.', 'Gwilin exhibits remarkable optimism and resilience, maintaining his cheerful disposition even in the face of his employer''s harsh criticism and the dangerous bear situation plaguing the mill. His philosophical outlook on life, inherited from his father, allows him to find contentment in his circumstances while maintaining an almost naive level of positivity that endears him to others.', 'Like most Bosmer, Gwilin has a smaller, lithe frame with the characteristic pointed ears and angular features of his race. His movements are naturally graceful and efficient, typical of Wood Elves, though years of physical labor have added some muscular definition to his slight build.', '* Temba Wide-Arm - His employer and mentor, though their relationship is strained by her harsh demeanor * Wilhelm - Innkeeper at Vilemyr Inn where he lodges * His Father - Though absent, remains a strong influence through his life teachings * Local Bears - Views them as a nuisance affecting his work, but lacks Temba''s intense hatred', 'As apprentice at Temba Wide-Arm''s sawmill, Gwilin performs various tasks including chopping firewood, operating the mill, and assisting with lumber processing. He lives permanently at the Vilemyr Inn, suggesting his position provides enough income to maintain stable lodging.', '* Proficient in woodcutting and lumber processing * Basic carpentry and mill operation abilities * Physical endurance from daily manual labor * Natural Bosmer archery talents, though likely rusty from disuse', 'Gwilin speaks with a gentle, cheerful tone that reflects his optimistic nature, often incorporating simple wisdom and positive observations about life. His speech patterns are clear and direct, showing more sophistication than might be expected from a manual laborer.', '* Master the art of lumber milling to potentially own his own sawmill someday * Maintain his philosophical approach to life despite daily challenges * Help resolve the bear problem in Ivarstead while keeping peace between Temba and the local wildlife * Find ways to blend his Bosmer heritage with his chosen life in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hadring', 'Hadring is a traditional Nord innkeeper who maintains his family''s legacy as the proprietor of the remote Nightgate Inn. Despite the inn''s isolation and sparse clientele, he maintains a welcoming and talkative demeanor, taking pride in continuing the establishment that has been passed down through generations of his family.', 'nord, innkeeper, pale', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into a family of innkeepers, Hadring inherited the Nightgate Inn from his father, continuing a tradition that spans back to his great-grandfather who built the establishment. Growing up in such an isolated location has given him a unique perspective on life and taught him to appreciate the value of good conversation with the occasional travelers who pass through.', 'Hadring is a naturally gregarious and talkative individual who enjoys engaging with his guests, sometimes to the point of being overly chatty. He displays a practical Nord''s skepticism toward magic while maintaining a tolerant attitude toward his diverse clientele, demonstrating a live-and-let-live philosophy as long as bills are paid. Despite the inn''s remote location and limited business, he maintains an optimistic and welcoming demeanor.', 'A typical Nord male with the sturdy build common to his race, weathered by years of living in Skyrim''s harsh climate. His features show signs of aging from decades of managing the inn, though he maintains the hardy constitution characteristic of Nord innkeepers.', '* Malaclob - Long-term Orc tenant whom he respects for his regular payments and peaceful demeanor * Fultheim - Regular patron who frequents the inn to drink away his troubles * Family Legacy - Maintains strong connection to his ancestors who built and ran the inn before him * Local Travelers - Maintains cordial relationships with occasional passing merchants and wanderers', 'Hadring serves as the owner and sole proprietor of the Nightgate Inn, personally handling all aspects of its operation including serving food and drink, maintaining rooms, and managing supplies. His position requires him to be cook, bartender, cleaner, and businessman all in one, though the limited clientele makes this manageable.', '* Experienced in all aspects of inn management and maintenance * Proficient in basic cooking and mead serving * Capable of basic self-defense with an iron dagger * Skilled conversationalist and story-teller * Knowledgeable about local geography and travel routes', 'Hadring speaks in a friendly, conversational tone typical of Nord innkeepers, often offering unsolicited information and engaging in small talk. His manner of speech is straightforward and informal, reflecting his rural Nordic upbringing.', '* Maintain his family''s legacy by keeping the Nightgate Inn operational despite limited business * Preserve the inn''s reputation as a reliable waypoint for travelers * Generate enough income to keep the establishment running through the harsh winters');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hadvar', 'Hadvar is a dutiful Imperial Legion soldier who demonstrates compassion and honor even while carrying out difficult orders. Despite his role in the player''s near-execution, he shows genuine remorse and proves himself a capable warrior and loyal ally during the dragon attack on Helgen.', 'imperial, warrior, whiterun, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born and raised in Riverwood under the care of his uncle Alvor, the town''s blacksmith, Hadvar chose to join the Imperial Legion at a young age. His military service took him from his small village life to become a respected soldier, eventually earning him a position handling prisoner processing and garrison duties at Helgen.', 'Hadvar exhibits a strong sense of duty balanced with compassion and pragmatism. Though loyal to the Empire, he shows regret when forced to participate in morally questionable actions and prioritizes protecting civilians over following strict protocol. He maintains a professional demeanor but displays genuine warmth toward those he trusts.', 'A sturdy Nord man with typical Nordic features including light skin and brown hair. He bears the weathered countenance of a soldier who has seen regular combat, with a strong build suited to wearing heavy armor. His face shows signs of exposure to Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Alvor - Beloved uncle who raised him and taught him basic smithing skills * General Tullius - Respected commanding officer in the Imperial Legion * Ralof - Former childhood friend turned adversary due to Civil War allegiances * Imperial Legion - Loyal soldier and dedicated member of the military force', 'Hadvar serves as a soldier in the Imperial Legion, where his duties include prisoner processing, garrison defense, and frontline combat. Following his escape from Helgen, he continues to serve with distinction in various military campaigns throughout the Civil War.', '* Proficient in both one-handed weapons and shield combat techniques * Trained in heavy armor use and battlefield tactics * Capable archer with standard military training * Basic knowledge of military logistics and prisoner processing procedures * Fundamental understanding of smithing learned from his uncle', 'Speaks with a mild Nordic accent and uses proper military terminology when appropriate. His tone is generally professional and respectful, though he can be more casual and friendly with those he trusts.', '* Advance within the ranks of the Imperial Legion through dedicated service * Help restore peace to Skyrim by ending the civil war * Protect his hometown of Riverwood and his uncle from the dangers of war * Maintain order and justice throughout the province under Imperial rule');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('haelga', 'Haelga is a complex and controversial figure in Riften who balances her public role as a stern bunkhouse owner with her secret life as a devout worshipper of Dibella. She embodies the duality between societal expectations and personal freedom, maintaining a facade of respectability while privately pursuing her passionate dedication to the Dibellan Arts.', 'nord, innkeeper, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Originally from an unknown part of Skyrim, Haelga established herself in Riften and opened the bunkhouse to provide lodging for working-class citizens. After her sister and brother-in-law were killed by bandits, she took in her orphaned niece Svana Far-Shield, saving her from life in an orphanage. While appearing to be a simple businesswoman, she has cultivated deep connections with Riften''s merchants and workers through both professional and intimate relationships.', 'Haelga is confident, unapologetic, and sometimes confrontational when challenged about her lifestyle or beliefs. She maintains a strict separation between her public and private personas, being businesslike during the day while pursuing pleasure and religious devotion at night. Though she can be harsh with her niece Svana, this stems from a practical worldview shaped by surviving in Riften''s harsh environment.', 'A mature Nord woman with the typical hardy physique of her race, though maintaining an attractive appearance befitting a devotee of Dibella. Her features likely show signs of Nordic heritage with fair skin and strong bone structure, while her movements carry both grace and authority.', '* Svana Far-Shield - Niece and reluctant employee, their relationship is strained by conflicting values * Bolli - Current lover and frequent companion at the Bee and Barb * Madesi - Craftsman who makes her Marks of Dibella, unaware of their true purpose * Various Lovers - Multiple partners throughout Riften with whom she practices the Dibellan Arts * Maven Black-Briar - Likely maintains a cautious relationship with Riften''s true power player', 'Haelga owns and operates Haelga''s Bunkhouse, providing affordable lodging for Riften''s working class. She manages all aspects of the business, from maintaining the building to collecting payments and managing employees, while also serving as the public face of the establishment.', '* Expert in the Dibellan Arts and religious practices of Dibella * Capable businesswoman with strong negotiation abilities * Adept at maintaining discretion and managing sensitive relationships * Basic combat abilities with a dagger for self-defense * Skilled in the art of seduction and persuasion', 'She speaks directly and authoritatively, often with a dismissive or stern tone toward strangers and a more sultry, intimate manner with those she favors. Her vocabulary and manner of speech reflect both her business acumen and her secret religious devotion.', '* Maintain and expand her business while keeping her religious practices secret from the general public * Continue practicing and perfecting her devotion to Dibella despite social prejudice * Secure her position in Riften''s social hierarchy * Eventually pass the bunkhouse business to a worthy successor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hafjorg', 'Hafjorg is a seasoned Nord apothecary who manages the day-to-day operations of Elgrim''s Elixirs alongside her husband in Riften''s canal district. Despite her advanced age, she maintains a sharp mind for alchemy and business, though she harbors persistent concerns about their shop''s damp location affecting their ingredients and merchandise.', 'nord, alchemist, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Hafjorg learned the art of alchemy in her youth, likely through apprenticeship or family tradition. She met and married Elgrim, combining their shared passion for alchemy into a successful business venture in Riften, though the city''s notorious corruption and their shop''s location in the lower canal district have presented ongoing challenges.', 'Hafjorg is a practical and diligent worker with a warm disposition toward customers, though she can be persistent in voicing her concerns about business matters. She demonstrates patience with her sometimes-difficult husband and maintains a professional demeanor despite operating in Riften''s less reputable district. Her occasional nagging about the shop''s location reveals an underlying perfectionism and concern for quality.', 'An elderly Nord woman with the weathered features typical of long-time alchemists exposed to various ingredients and fumes. Her hands show the characteristic staining and calluses of someone who has spent decades grinding herbs and mixing potions.', '* Elgrim - Husband and business partner, shares her passion for alchemy * Filnjar - Business contact in Shor''s Stone who supplies ore samples * Various Riften merchants - Professional acquaintances in the marketplace * Regular customers - Maintains cordial relationships with repeat buyers', 'Hafjorg serves as both proprietor and master alchemist at Elgrim''s Elixirs, handling most customer interactions and maintaining inventory. She manages the shop''s day-to-day operations while also crafting potions and maintaining relationships with suppliers.', '* Expert knowledge of alchemy and potion-making * Proficient at identifying and preserving alchemical ingredients * Business management and merchant skills * Basic knowledge of ore properties and their alchemical applications', 'Speaks with the direct, no-nonsense manner common to Nord merchants, though maintains a warm undertone with regular customers. Her speech often includes references to alchemical terms and occasional complaints about the dampness affecting their goods.', '* Relocate the shop to a drier location in Riften to better preserve their ingredients * Maintain the quality and reputation of Elgrim''s Elixirs despite challenging conditions * Secure reliable sources of rare alchemical ingredients * Support her husband''s alchemical research while keeping the business profitable');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hafnar_ice-fist', 'Hafnar Ice-Fist was a talented Nord mage from the College of Winterhold who met a tragic end during an ill-fated expedition to Labyrinthian. His fate was sealed by the betrayal of Savos Aren, who sacrificed him and Atmah to contain the dragon priest Morokei, leaving them eternally bound as magical sentinels.', 'nord, mage, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into a Nord family that likely challenged traditional warrior culture by pursuing magic, Hafnar studied at the College of Winterhold and showed particular promise in magical arts despite his heritage. His nickname ''Ice-Fist'' suggests a specialization in frost magic or perhaps a unique combat style combining Nordic martial prowess with magical abilities. He joined an ambitious expedition to Labyrinthian led by fellow mage Savos Aren, seeking ancient artifacts and knowledge.', 'Hafnar displayed a pragmatic and cautious nature, often questioning the group''s decisions and expressing skepticism about their chances of success. Despite his reservations, he showed strong loyalty to his companions and considerable bravery in the face of danger. His ghost''s dialogue reveals someone who valued survival over glory but wouldn''t abandon his companions.', 'As a Nord mage, Hafnar likely possessed the typical robust Nordic build while maintaining the scholarly bearing of a trained mage. His ghost appears as a tall, broad-shouldered figure with the characteristic Nordic features common to his race.', '* Savos Aren - Fellow expedition member who ultimately betrayed him * Atmah - Close companion who shared his final fate * Takes-In-Light - Fellow expedition member who perished before him * Elvali Veren - Colleague from the expedition who died in Labyrinthian * Girduin - Fellow mage who was the first to fall during the expedition * College of Winterhold - His academic home and professional association', 'Hafnar served as a mage of the College of Winterhold, likely holding a position as a researcher or scholar. His participation in the Labyrinthian expedition suggests he was considered among the more capable mages at the College.', '* Proficient in frost magic, as suggested by his surname * College-trained magical abilities across multiple schools of magic * Likely skilled in Nordic combat traditions combined with magical arts * Archaeological and historical knowledge relating to ancient Nordic ruins * Survival skills necessary for dangerous expeditions', 'Hafnar speaks with a practical, direct manner typical of Nords, though tempered by magical education. His dialogue reveals someone who voices concerns openly but remains respectful of his peers.', '* Uncover powerful artifacts and knowledge within Labyrinthian * Advance his understanding of ancient Nordic magic * Survive the expedition and return to the College * Prove himself as a Nord mage in a culture that typically distrusts magic');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hajvarr_iron-hand', 'Hajvarr Iron-Hand is a formidable Nord bandit leader who commands respect through both fear and loyalty from his base at White River Watch. Known throughout Whiterun Hold for his ruthlessness in raids yet maintaining a peculiar sense of honor, particularly in his protection of his blind uncle, he has established himself as one of the most notorious bandits in the region.', 'nord, thief, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into a Nord family that likely fell on hard times, Hajvarr turned to banditry at a young age and quickly rose through the ranks due to his natural leadership abilities and combat prowess. He established his reputation through successful raids and strategic thinking, eventually taking control of White River Watch and transforming it into a well-organized bandit stronghold. His most defining characteristic came from his exceptional skill with two-handed weapons, earning him the moniker ''Iron-Hand.''', 'Hajvarr is a complex figure who balances ruthless leadership with a strong sense of personal loyalty, particularly evident in his protective relationship with his blind uncle. While he maintains control through intimidation and force, he also shows a sophisticated understanding of group dynamics and leadership, as evidenced by his written warnings to those who would mock his uncle. His journal entries reveal a thoughtful, literate man who carefully considers the consequences of his actions.', 'A sturdy, battle-hardened Nord with the muscular build typical of those who favor two-handed weapons. His face bears the scars of numerous battles, and his hands are notably calloused from years of wielding heavy weapons. His physical presence commands attention, with the bearing of someone accustomed to being obeyed.', '* Ulfr the Blind - Beloved uncle whom he fiercely protects from ridicule and harm * Rodulf - Subordinate bandit whom he''s warned about mocking Ulfr * White River Watch Bandits - Loyal followers who respect and fear him * Whiterun Guard - Enemies who seek his capture but haven''t yet succeeded * Whiterun Jarl - Authority figure who wants him driven from the hold', 'As the leader of the White River Watch bandits, Hajvarr organizes raids, manages loot distribution, and maintains order among his crew. He operates from a strategic position overlooking the White River, coordinating bandit activities throughout the region while maintaining a relatively sophisticated operation compared to typical bandit groups.', '* Master of two-handed combat, particularly skilled with heavy weapons * Natural leader with strong tactical and strategic abilities * Capable of maintaining discipline among a diverse group of bandits * Literate and educated enough to maintain detailed journals and written correspondence * Experienced in survival and mountainous terrain navigation', 'Speaks with a commanding, gravelly Nordic accent, using direct and often threatening language to maintain his authority. His vocabulary reveals more education than the typical bandit, though he maintains a rough manner of speaking to relate to his followers.', '* Maintain and expand his bandit operation''s territory and influence * Protect his uncle Ulfr while keeping order among his followers * Accumulate enough wealth to potentially establish a more legitimate power base * Avoid capture by Whiterun''s guards while maintaining his reputation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hakon_one-eye', 'Hakon One-Eye was one of the most legendary Nord heroes of the Merethic Era, renowned for his pivotal role in the Dragon War and the first defeat of Alduin. As a member of the original Tongues alongside Gormlaith Golden-Hilt and Felldir the Old, he helped develop and execute the desperate plan to use an Elder Scroll against the World-Eater, ultimately securing humanity''s survival against dragon dominion.', 'nord, warrior, dragon', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born during the Merethic Era when dragons ruled over mankind, Hakon rose to prominence as one of the first human masters of the Thu''um. He lost his eye in an early battle against the dragons, earning his namesake and battle-scarred appearance. His leadership and strategic mind proved crucial in organizing the human rebellion against dragon rule, culminating in the legendary battle atop the Throat of the World.', 'Hakon is a pragmatic and measured warrior who balances Gormlaith''s fierce bloodlust with Felldir''s scholarly caution. Though a fearsome fighter, he shows deep concern for the broader strategic picture and the lives of those under his command. His initial reluctance to use the Elder Scroll demonstrates both his preference for honorable direct combat and his wisdom in recognizing when desperate measures become necessary.', 'A tall, muscular Nord warrior bearing numerous battle scars, most notably the missing eye that earned him his moniker. His remaining eye holds the intense gaze of a veteran commander, and his face shows the weathering of countless battles. His powerful frame and commanding presence reflect his lifetime of combat against dragons.', '* Gormlaith Golden-Hilt - Fellow Tongue and close companion, whose aggressive nature he often tempers with caution * Felldir the Old - Respected ally and fellow Tongue, though sometimes at odds over tactical decisions * Last Dragonborn - Crucial ally in the final battle against Alduin in Sovngarde * Alduin - Arch-nemesis and primary antagonist whom he fought across multiple eras', 'As one of the original Tongues, Hakon served as both a warrior-leader in the rebellion against dragon rule and a master of the Voice. In death, he continues his role as a legendary hero in the Hall of Valor, standing ready to aid the Last Dragonborn in the final battle against Alduin.', '* Master of the Thu''um, capable of using multiple dragon shouts including Dragonrend * Expert warrior specializing in traditional Nord combat techniques * Tactical and strategic military commander * Battle Cry power that can cause enemies to flee * Proficient with traditional Nord weapons, particularly the battle axe', 'Hakon speaks with a deep, commanding voice befitting a Nord hero, using formal, archaic language that reflects his ancient origins. His tone is often serious and measured, though capable of battlefield rallying cries when needed.', '* Ensure the final defeat of Alduin and the protection of both the mortal world and Sovngarde * Aid the Last Dragonborn in fulfilling their destiny * Maintain eternal vigilance in the Hall of Valor against threats to Sovngarde * Preserve the ancient traditions and honor of the Nordic people');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('halbarn_iron-fur', 'Halbarn Iron-Fur is a skilled Nord blacksmith and valued member of the Thirsk Mead Hall community who demonstrates remarkable resilience and craftsmanship despite challenging circumstances. His expertise in metalworking and dedication to his craft make him an essential figure in maintaining the hall''s equipment and defenses.', 'nord, blacksmith, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Solstheim, Halbarn learned the art of blacksmithing from an early age and eventually became the primary smith for Thirsk Mead Hall. After the Riekling invasion forced him and his fellow Nords from their home, he maintained his determination to reclaim the hall and restore his forge to its former glory.', 'Halbarn is a practical and dedicated craftsman who takes great pride in his work and values quality above all else. He shows unwavering loyalty to his fellow Thirsk residents while maintaining a pragmatic outlook on leadership and community matters. Despite hardships, he maintains a stoic demeanor typical of Nord craftsmen.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the muscular build typical of a blacksmith, featuring callused hands and strong arms from years of working the forge. His face bears minor burn scars from his craft, and his body shows the weathering of someone who has spent years in Solstheim''s harsh climate.', '* Bujold - Former leader of Thirsk whom he respects but accepts the judgment against * Elmus - Close colleague who helps maintain the hall''s facilities * Kuvar - Regular client for whom he crafts armor * Skaal Village - Maintains trading relationships for materials * Raven Rock Merchants - Business connections for acquiring raw materials', 'As Thirsk''s resident blacksmith, Halbarn is responsible for crafting and maintaining the weapons and armor for the hall''s residents. He operates the hall''s forge and manages the procurement of materials through his network of contacts across Solstheim.', '* Expert blacksmithing with specialization in Nordic-style weaponry and armor * Proficient in working with rare materials like Stalhrim and ebony * Skilled warrior capable of wielding heavy weapons, particularly warhammers * Knowledge of material procurement and trading * Basic survival skills necessary for life in Solstheim', 'Speaks in a direct, practical manner with the typical Nordic accent, often relating conversations back to his craft or the forge. His speech patterns reflect his straightforward nature and professional pride.', '* Restore Thirsk''s forge to its former glory after the Riekling occupation * Maintain the hall''s defensive capabilities through quality arms and armor * Expand his crafting expertise, particularly with rare materials like Stalhrim * Establish a more reliable supply chain for crafting materials * Find a worthy partner to share his life and craft with');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('haldyn', 'Haldyn is a formidable Redguard elemental mage who rules over the Blood Horkers pirate gang from their stronghold on Japhet''s Folly. As a ruthless leader who has terrorized the Sea of Ghosts, he combines powerful destruction magic with tactical cunning to maintain his crew''s feared reputation in the northern waters of Skyrim.', 'redguard, mage, sailor, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally trained as a battlemage in Hammerfell, Haldyn discovered that his magical talents could bring him greater wealth through piracy than legitimate employment. He gradually built up the Blood Horkers from a small gang into a feared pirate organization, choosing the remote Japhet''s Folly as his base of operations to avoid interference from the authorities while maintaining strategic control over shipping routes.', 'Haldyn is cruel, arrogant, and takes sadistic pleasure in asserting his dominance over others. He views most people as beneath him and relies on intimidation to maintain control over his crew. Despite his aggressive nature, he is a calculating strategist who has successfully evaded capture by carefully choosing targets and maintaining a secure island fortress.', 'A tall, muscular Redguard with weathered dark skin bearing numerous battle scars from years of piracy. His face shows the hardened features typical of his race, with sharp eyes that gleam with cruel intelligence and a closely-cropped black beard streaked with grey.', '* Blood Horkers - Leader and commander of the pirate crew * East Empire Company - Sworn enemies due to repeated attacks on their vessels * Adelaisa Vendicci - Primary antagonist seeking his death * Local Pirates - Respected and feared among other pirate groups in the region', 'Haldyn serves as both the leader of the Blood Horkers and the master of Japhet''s Folly. He personally oversees major raids on merchant vessels while managing his crew''s operations and maintaining their stronghold''s defenses.', '* Master of Destruction magic, particularly skilled with shock spells * Experienced tactician and naval commander * Proficient in heavy armor combat techniques * Natural leader with strong intimidation abilities * Skilled navigator and seafarer', 'Speaks with a deep, menacing voice that carries both authority and contempt. His speech is direct and often threatening, peppered with cruel taunts and condescending remarks.', '* Maintain and expand the Blood Horkers'' dominance over the Sea of Ghosts * Accumulate greater wealth and power through piracy * Strengthen his fortress on Japhet''s Folly to be impregnable * Eliminate any threats to his authority and position');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('halldir', 'Halldir is an ancient and powerful draugr mage who has transformed his burial cairn into a sinister lair where he drains the life force from unwary travelers. Through centuries of dark magical practices and stolen life essence, he has maintained a state between life and death while pursuing full resurrection, making him one of Skyrim''s most formidable and feared undead spellcasters.', 'nord, warrior', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a powerful Nordic mage from the First Era, Halldir''s obsession with immortality led him to delve into forbidden magic and necromantic arts. After his physical death, he used his magical prowess to maintain consciousness and began stealing life force from victims to preserve his existence, gradually transforming his burial site into a deadly magical nexus. His centuries of absorbing life essence have granted him unique abilities, including the power to split himself into elemental aspects.', 'Halldir is coldly calculating and utterly ruthless in his pursuit of restored life, viewing living beings merely as resources to be harvested. His long undeath has stripped away most human emotions, leaving him with an alien mindset focused solely on his goals. He shows sadistic pleasure in tormenting his victims, often toying with them before draining their life force.', 'In his corporeal form, Halldir appears as a tall, imposing draugr with deeply sunken features and desiccated gray skin pulled tight over ancient bones. His eyes burn with an unnatural blue fire, and wisps of stolen life energy occasionally emanate from his withered form. His movements are unnaturally fluid for a draugr, suggesting his enhanced state of undeath.', '* Adventurer Victims - Countless travelers he has drained over centuries * Local Nords - Those who know of his cairn warn others to stay away * Other Draugr - Commands lesser undead within his cairn * Ancient Nordic Mages - Former peers from when he was alive, all long dead', 'Halldir serves as both guardian and master of his own burial cairn, maintaining the magical energies that preserve his existence while defending against intruders. His primary activity involves luring in and draining the life force from travelers, using complex magical rituals to harness their essence.', '* Master-level Destruction magic specializing in frost, fire, and lightning * Expert necromancer with unique abilities in life force manipulation * Capable of splitting into three elemental aspects during combat * Advanced knowledge of ancient Nordic magic and ritual practices * Skilled in soul manipulation and life essence drainage', 'Halldir speaks in ancient Nordic, his voice a hollow, ethereal whisper that echoes with supernatural power. His speech is formal and archaic, often mixing threats and taunts with fragments of long-dead magical incantations.', '* Gather enough life force to fully restore himself to living form * Perfect his mastery over life essence manipulation * Expand his influence beyond his cairn once restored * Achieve true immortality in a living form rather than undeath');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hamal', 'Hamal is a respected Nord priestess who serves as the Mother of the Temple of Dibella in Markarth, overseeing its sacred traditions and ceremonies. As master of the Inner Sanctum, she maintains strict adherence to religious protocols while guarding ancient secrets of enchanting and divine communion.', 'nord, priest, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth, Hamal dedicated her life to Dibella''s service from an early age, rising through the temple hierarchy through decades of devoted study and practice. Her mastery of enchanting and deep understanding of Dibellan mysteries eventually earned her the position of Mother, making her responsible for maintaining the temple''s traditions and protecting its most sacred artifact - the Heart of Dibella.', 'Hamal is stern, authoritative, and uncompromising when it comes to temple rules and traditions, showing particular disdain for uninitiated intruders. Despite her severe exterior, she demonstrates wisdom in knowing when to show mercy and pragmatism in accepting help from outsiders when necessary. Her dedication to Dibella''s teachings shapes every aspect of her character.', 'A mature Nord woman with the dignified bearing of a high priestess, showing signs of age but maintaining a graceful demeanor. Her features are sharp and angular, typical of her Nordic heritage, with keen eyes that miss little within her temple''s walls.', '* Other Dibella Priestesses - Acts as their spiritual mother and guide * The Sybil - Responsible for protecting and nurturing the temple''s divine oracle * Citizens of Markarth - Maintains formal but distant relationships as befits her station * Temple Guards - Commands their loyalty in protecting the Inner Sanctum', 'As Mother of the Temple of Dibella, Hamal oversees all religious ceremonies, maintains sacred artifacts, and guards divine mysteries. She serves as master trainer in Enchanting, sharing her expertise with those who prove worthy, while managing the temple''s daily operations and protecting its most sacred spaces.', '* Master-level knowledge of Enchanting, including rare and sacred techniques * Expert in Dibellan religious ceremonies and protocols * Proficient in restoration magic related to temple blessings * Administrative and leadership abilities in managing the temple * Basic combat training for self-defense, particularly with war axes', 'Speaks with formal authority, using precise religious terminology and maintaining a tone of superiority and wisdom. Her manner of speech reflects her position as Mother, being both commanding and instructive.', '* Protect the sanctity of the Temple of Dibella and its sacred artifacts * Guide and nurture the next generation of priestesses * Maintain the ancient traditions and ceremonies of Dibella * Find and train a worthy successor to eventually take her place as Mother');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hamelyn', 'Hamelyn is a deranged Breton wizard and former College of Winterhold apprentice who has devoted himself to breeding an army of venomous skeevers in the basement of Honningbrew Meadery. Driven by perceived persecution and a thirst for revenge, he combines his alchemical knowledge with dark ambitions to create increasingly dangerous mutations while unknowingly serving as a pawn in a larger scheme to sabotage the meadery.', 'breton, thief, mage, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally imprisoned in Whiterun for a decade due to his dangerous experiments and unstable behavior, Hamelyn later sought legitimate recognition by enrolling at the College of Winterhold as an alchemist apprentice. His time there ended in expulsion after conflicts with instructors who he believed were jealous of his abilities, though records suggest his experiments had become increasingly unethical and dangerous. After escaping custody, he found refuge in Honningbrew''s basement where the available ingredients allowed him to continue his twisted research.', 'Hamelyn exhibits clear signs of paranoid delusions and megalomania, convinced of his own genius while attributing any setbacks to persecution by jealous rivals. His isolation and past traumas have warped his worldview, leading him to seek revenge through increasingly desperate and dangerous means. Despite his mental instability, he maintains enough clarity to conduct complex alchemical experiments and manipulate his skeever subjects.', 'A gaunt Breton man with wild, unkempt hair and dark-circled eyes betraying years of obsessive work and minimal sleep. His hands are covered in chemical burns and bite marks from his experiments, while his hunched posture suggests long hours bent over his alchemy table.', '* College of Winterhold Faculty - Former instructors he believes persecuted him out of jealousy * Mallus Maccius - Meadery employee secretly using his skeever experiments for sabotage * Sabjorn - Unknowing meadery owner whose business he''s helping destroy * Venomfang Skeevers - Considers his mutated creatures his ''children'' and loyal army', 'Hamelyn operates as a rogue alchemist and skeever breeder, conducting unauthorized experiments in the meadery''s basement. His work combines legitimate alchemical research with dangerous mutations, while unknowingly serving as a tool in Maven Black-Briar''s scheme to eliminate business competition.', '* Advanced knowledge of alchemy, particularly in creating venoms and mutations * Proficient in Restoration, Alteration, and Destruction magic * Expert in skeever breeding and behavioral conditioning * Capable of creating complex chemical formulas from limited ingredients', 'His speech patterns are erratic and intense, often shifting between scholarly terminology and paranoid ramblings about persecution and revenge. He frequently refers to his skeevers as his ''children'' and speaks with particular venom about the College faculty who ''betrayed'' him.', '* Create an unstoppable army of venomous skeevers to exact revenge on those who wronged him * Prove his genius to the academic community that rejected him * Perfect his alchemical formulas for skeever enhancement * Eventually return to the College of Winterhold in triumph over his former persecutors');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('haran', 'Haran is a hardworking Nord innkeeper who, alongside her husband Dagur, maintains The Frozen Hearth inn in the declining town of Winterhold. She represents the resilient spirit of those who remained in Winterhold after its collapse, balancing the challenges of running a business in a dying town with maintaining her family''s livelihood.', 'nord, innkeeper, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Haran settled in Winterhold before the Great Collapse, likely drawn by the town''s former prosperity when it was the capital of the hold. She witnessed the town''s dramatic decline following the Great Collapse but chose to remain, adapting to the harsh new reality of running an inn in a nearly abandoned town that relies almost entirely on College visitors for survival.', 'Pragmatic and direct, Haran approaches life with a no-nonsense attitude shaped by years of hardship in Winterhold. She maintains a cautious disposition toward strangers while showing loyalty to her family and remaining customers, though she''s grown increasingly hardened by the challenge of managing difficult patrons like Ranmir.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the weathered features typical of those who brave Winterhold''s harsh climate. Her hands show the calluses and wear of someone who works long hours maintaining an inn, while her face bears the subtle signs of stress from years of difficult work.', '* Dagur - Husband and business partner in running The Frozen Hearth * Eirid - Her beloved daughter who lives with them at the inn * Ranmir - Problematic regular customer who owes substantial debt to the inn * College of Winterhold - Primary source of business, though maintains a cautious distance * Winterhold Residents - Limited but important relationships with the few remaining townspeople', 'Haran serves as co-proprietor of The Frozen Hearth inn, working extensive hours from 9am to 2am daily. She handles food service, customer relations, and general maintenance of the establishment, while also managing the inn''s finances and dealing with difficult customers.', '* Experienced in food preparation and preservation techniques * Proficient in business management and accounting * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Skilled in customer service and conflict resolution * Expert knowledge of local gossip and College-related news', 'Haran speaks in a direct, unembellished manner typical of Nord innkeepers, often cutting straight to the point without unnecessary pleasantries. Her tone carries a hint of weariness but maintains professional courtesy, especially when addressing potential customers.', '* Maintain a profitable business despite Winterhold''s declining population * Secure a stable future for her daughter Eirid in the struggling town * Collect outstanding debts from problematic customers like Ranmir * Keep the inn as a respectable establishment despite the town''s difficulties');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lord_harkon', 'Lord Harkon is an ancient Nordic pure-blood vampire and the formidable leader of the Volkihar vampire clan, wielding immense power as one of the first vampires blessed directly by Molag Bal. A former king turned immortal being, he seeks to fulfill an ancient prophecy to blot out the sun using Auriel''s Bow and his daughter''s blood, demonstrating his ruthless dedication to vampire supremacy.', 'nord, skyrimall, volkihar, vampire, daedric', '', '', 'sk_harkon', '', 'Originally a powerful Nordic king with vast territories, Harkon sacrificed a thousand innocents to Molag Bal to gain immortality for himself and his family, becoming the first of the Volkihar vampire bloodline. His obsession with power and eternal life eventually led to the deterioration of his marriage to Valerica, while his discovery of the Tyranny of the Sun prophecy became his all-consuming purpose.', 'Harkon is deeply arrogant and elitist, viewing pure-blood vampires as superior beings and considering all others, including ''lesser'' vampires, as inferior creatures. He displays a calculating and ruthless nature, willing to sacrifice even his own daughter to achieve his goals, while maintaining a facade of aristocratic sophistication that barely masks his cruel and power-hungry core.', 'A tall, imposing Nordic male with sharp, aristocratic features and the characteristic glowing eyes of a vampire lord. In his vampire lord form, he takes on a uniquely terrifying appearance with grey-blue skin, massive bat-like wings, and elongated claws that set him apart from other vampire lords.', '* Serana - His daughter, whom he views more as a means to an end than family * Valerica - His estranged wife who betrayed him to protect Serana * Volkihar Clan - His loyal vampire followers who serve him as their lord and master * Dawnguard - Sworn enemies who seek to prevent his prophecy from being fulfilled * Molag Bal - The Daedric Prince who granted him vampirism, whom he serves', 'Lord Harkon serves as the supreme leader of the Volkihar vampire clan, ruling from their ancient castle stronghold. He maintains his position through both political maneuvering among vampire courtiers and the sheer force of his supernatural powers, while directing his clan''s efforts to fulfill the prophecy.', '* Master of vampire magic and blood rituals * Unique and powerful vampire lord transformation abilities * Expert swordsman with centuries of combat experience * Advanced knowledge of ancient prophecies and arcane lore * Exceptional leadership and tactical planning abilities * Powerful mental domination and manipulation capabilities', 'Speaks with an aristocratic, commanding tone that reflects his ancient noble heritage and absolute authority. His speech is formal and sophisticated, often tinged with condescension and thinly-veiled threats.', '* Complete the Tyranny of the Sun prophecy to eliminate the sun''s threat to vampires * Maintain and expand the power of the Volkihar vampire clan * Exact revenge on Valerica for her betrayal * Establish vampires as the dominant species in Tamriel * Acquire Auriel''s Bow to fulfill his destiny');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('harlaug', 'Harlaug is a seasoned Nord ferryman operating out of Dawnstar, known for his willingness to brave treacherous waters that other sailors avoid. Despite his gruff exterior, he demonstrates quiet courage in transporting passengers to dangerous locations like Giant''s Tooth, though he ensures his risk is well-compensated.', 'nord, peasant, pale, haafingar, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh coastal region of The Pale, Harlaug learned seafaring from his father who operated boats along Skyrim''s northern coast. After years of witnessing numerous sailors disappear near cursed locations like Giant''s Tooth, he developed a healthy respect for the supernatural dangers of Skyrim''s waters while maintaining the Nord determination to face such challenges head-on.', 'Harlaug exhibits a gruff, no-nonsense demeanor typical of Nord sailors, preferring direct communication and honest dealings. Though he appears harsh and mercenary in his dealings, he shows an underlying sense of duty by being willing to transport passengers to dangerous locations that other ferrymen avoid, demonstrating a complex balance between profit-seeking and courage.', 'A weathered Nord of average height with a sturdy, sailor''s build shaped by years of rowing and working on boats. His skin is tanned and roughened by constant exposure to sea spray and harsh northern winds, with callused hands from years of handling ropes and oars.', '* Thoring - Professional relationship with the Windpeak Inn''s innkeeper * Other Ferrymen - Respected for taking risks they won''t * Dawnstar Guards - Maintains cordial relationships to ensure smooth business operations * Local Fishermen - Shares information about weather conditions and dangerous waters', 'Harlaug serves as Dawnstar''s primary ferryman, operating a passenger boat service that connects various coastal settlements including Solitude and Windhelm. He specializes in dangerous routes that other sailors avoid, particularly transport to the cursed island of Giant''s Tooth, charging premium rates for such risky ventures.', '* Expert navigation of Skyrim''s treacherous northern waters * Skilled sailor capable of handling rough seas and harsh weather * Proficient with basic weapons for self-defense at sea * Knowledge of coastal geography and dangerous maritime locations * Weather prediction and seamanship', 'Speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner with the typical Nord accent, often making blunt observations about weather conditions or warning of dangers ahead. His vocabulary is simple but precise, focused on practical matters of sailing and business.', '* Maintain a profitable ferry business while avoiding supernatural dangers * Save enough gold to eventually purchase a larger vessel * Continue building his reputation as the go-to ferryman for dangerous routes * Survive long enough to retire despite taking risky jobs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('harald', 'Harald is a Nord miner in Dawnstar whose mundane facade conceals a darker reality as an unwitting thrall to the vampire Fenrik. While appearing to be a simple laborer at the Quicksilver Mine, he unknowingly serves a sinister Daedric cult dedicated to Molag Bal, carrying out his master''s bidding without awareness of his own enslavement.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a common laborer who came to Dawnstar seeking steady work in the mines, Harald fell victim to Fenrik''s vampiric influence through either chance encounter or careful targeting. His enslavement likely occurred gradually, with Fenrik using his vampiric powers to slowly dominate Harald''s will while maintaining the miner''s ordinary routine as a cover for cult activities.', 'Under thralldom, Harald exhibits a dulled, somewhat mechanical demeanor while maintaining just enough normalcy to avoid suspicion. His true personality lies buried beneath Fenrik''s influence, though occasional moments of confusion or internal struggle might surface when his actions conflict with his former nature. He follows a strict routine and appears withdrawn, speaking only when necessary.', 'Harald is a sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of a career miner. His complexion is notably pale from working underground, with calloused hands and strong features characteristic of his Nordic heritage. Dark circles under his eyes and a slightly vacant stare hint at his thralled condition.', '* Fenrik - Vampire master who controls him through thralldom * Fellow Miners - Maintains minimal but cordial working relationships to avoid suspicion * Thoring - Employer at the mine who considers him a reliable worker * Cult Members - Unwitting association through Fenrik''s influence * Vigilants of Stendarr - Unknowing enemies due to his forced involvement in cult activities', 'Harald works as a miner in Dawnstar''s Quicksilver Mine, maintaining a convincing cover for his involuntary involvement in Fenrik''s cult activities. His daily routine involves legitimate mining work during regular hours, while his nights are spent unknowingly serving his master''s dark purposes.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of ore extraction and mining safety * Physical strength and endurance developed through years of manual labor * Unconscious ability to access secret passages and perform cult-related tasks while under thrall influence * Basic combat abilities with mining tools and daggers', 'Harald speaks in short, direct sentences with a traditional Nordic accent, though his voice often carries a distant, slightly distracted quality due to his thralled state. His responses tend to be minimal and practical, focusing mainly on his mining work to deflect deeper conversation.', '* Survive daily life while unknowingly serving Fenrik''s will * Maintain his cover as an ordinary miner in Dawnstar * Deep within his suppressed consciousness, a desire to break free from Fenrik''s control remains * Continue providing access to the mine''s secret chambers for cult activities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('harrald', 'Harrald is the privileged and politically zealous son of Jarl Laila Law-Giver of Riften, embodying the fierce Nordic nationalism of the Stormcloak cause. As heir apparent to Riften''s throne, he represents the next generation of hardline anti-Imperial leadership, demonstrated by his willingness to execute his own brother for Imperial sympathies.', 'nord, warrior, rift, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born into nobility as the eldest son of Jarl Laila Law-Giver, Harrald was raised in the opulent halls of Mistveil Keep with all the privileges and expectations of a future ruler. His upbringing during the growing tensions between the Empire and Skyrim shaped his extreme nationalist views, while his mother''s position as Jarl cultivated his sense of superiority and entitlement.', 'Harrald is arrogant, xenophobic, and utterly convinced of the righteousness of the Stormcloak cause, viewing any sympathy toward the Empire as treasonous. His privileged upbringing has made him haughty and dismissive of those he considers beneath him, while his fanatical nationalism has poisoned even his familial relationships. He shows unwavering loyalty to his mother and the Stormcloak ideology, even if it means advocating violence against his own brother.', 'A proud Nord warrior with the characteristic strong build and hardy constitution of his race. His bearing and posture reflect his noble upbringing, always standing tall with his chin raised in an imperious manner. His features likely bear the sharp, angular characteristics common to the Law-Giver bloodline.', '* Jarl Laila Law-Giver - His mother and ruler of Riften, whom he loyally supports * Saerlund - His brother whom he has disowned for Imperial sympathies and would execute if he were Jarl * Balimund - Local blacksmith he considers beneath him despite relying on his services * Stormcloak Leadership - Strong allies and ideological partners * Imperial Supporters - Considered enemies and potential traitors to Skyrim', 'As the son of the Jarl, Harrald holds no formal position but serves as heir apparent to Riften''s throne. He spends his days training in combat and observing the city''s defenses, viewing himself as a future military leader of the hold. His privileged position allows him to focus on martial training and political matters rather than requiring actual employment.', '* Trained warrior proficient with one-handed weapons, particularly swords * Experienced in Nordic combat techniques from years of training * Basic understanding of military strategy and tactics * Leadership capabilities developed through his position as the Jarl''s son * Political acumen gained from exposure to his mother''s court', 'Harrald speaks in an imperious, formal tone befitting his noble status, often using dismissive and condescending language with those he considers beneath him. His speech patterns reflect both his education and arrogance, frequently emphasizing his position as the Jarl''s son.', '* Succeed his mother as Jarl of Riften and maintain the hold''s allegiance to the Stormcloak cause * Purge Riften of Imperial influence and sympathizers * Prove himself as a worthy heir through martial prowess and political leadership * Defend Skyrim''s independence and traditional Nordic values');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hathrasil', 'Hathrasil is a downtrodden Breton laborer who works long hours at Markarth''s silver smelter, embodying the harsh realities of life for the working class in the city. His reserved nature and minimal social interactions reflect years of oppression under the Silver-Blood family''s economic dominance and the brutal oversight of his Orcish supervisor.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born into Markarth''s lower class, Hathrasil has spent over a decade working at the silver smelter, having likely taken the job during the Silver-Blood family''s consolidation of power after the Forsworn Uprising. His possession of Omluag''s room key suggests a longer history in the Warrens, possibly having helped establish the worker housing system.', 'Hathrasil is notably taciturn and resigned to his fate, displaying signs of long-term psychological wear from years of harsh working conditions and intimidation. His minimal responses and avoidance of controversial topics suggest someone who has learned to survive through invisibility and compliance, though his warning to Omluag about molten metal reveals a underlying sense of camaraderie with his fellow workers.', 'A middle-aged Breton male with the weathered appearance typical of manual laborers, likely bearing callused hands and burn scars from years of working with molten metal. His posture likely shows the physical toll of long hours at the smelter, with a slightly hunched stance and prematurely aged features.', '* Omluag - Long-term coworker of over 10 years, sharing a complex relationship of minimal verbal interaction but mutual understanding * Mulush - Oppressive Orcish supervisor whom he fears and obeys without question * Silver-Blood Family - Distant but impactful employers who control his livelihood * Other Warrens Residents - Fellow laborers with whom he shares living space but minimal social interaction', 'Hathrasil works as a silver smelter at Left Hand Mine''s smelting operation, processing silver ore into refined metal under the supervision of Mulush gro-Shugurz. His position represents the lowest tier of Markarth''s workforce, involving dangerous and exhausting labor for minimal compensation.', '* Experienced metalworker with extensive knowledge of silver smelting techniques * Physical endurance developed from years of manual labor * Basic survival skills necessary for life in the harsh conditions of the Warrens * Ability to remain inconspicuous and avoid confrontation', 'Hathrasil speaks in extremely brief, often monosyllabic responses, frequently deflecting questions or referring inquiries to authority figures. His speech pattern reflects both caution and resignation, avoiding any statements that could draw attention or cause trouble.', '* Maintain steady employment at the smelter to ensure basic survival * Avoid drawing attention from supervisors or the Silver-Blood family * Preserve what little security he has in his position at the smelter * Survive each day without injury or confrontation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('headless_horseman', 'The Headless Horseman is a mysterious spectral warrior who eternally rides through Skyrim''s dark nights, bearing the tragic mark of a violent death that left him without his head. As one of Skyrim''s most enigmatic supernatural entities, he serves as both guide and guardian to the ancient burial ground of Hamvir''s Rest, where his mortal remains are believed to lie.', 'skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Once a noble Nordic warrior who met a violent end through decapitation, possibly during the Civil War or an earlier conflict in Skyrim''s history. Though his true identity has been lost to time, legends suggest he was a respected military commander or thane who was betrayed and executed, his spirit now bound to guard the sacred grounds where fallen warriors rest.', 'Solemn and purposeful, the Horseman maintains a dignified bearing despite his grotesque fate. Though largely silent, his few utterances reveal a melancholic acceptance of his eternal duty, combined with a warrior''s pride that persists beyond death. His methodical patrolling patterns suggest a strong sense of duty that transcends mortality.', 'A tall, spectral figure whose translucent form bears the build of a Nordic warrior, made distinctive by the complete absence of a head above his shoulders. His ethereal body emanates a ghostly blue glow, and despite his incorporeal nature, he maintains the proud posture of a skilled horseman.', '* Hamvir''s Rest - Sacred burial ground he appears bound to protect * Ancient Nordic Warriors - Fellow fallen warriors whose remains rest at Hamvir''s Rest * His Spectral Steed - Eternal companion in his endless nocturnal rides * Living Warriors - Shows occasional acknowledgment of those who follow his path with warrior''s courage', 'Eternal guardian of Hamvir''s Rest, conducting nightly patrols through Skyrim''s wilderness to guide worthy warriors to this sacred burial ground. His spectral presence serves as both warning and waypoint for those who encounter him in the dark hours.', '* Master horsemanship that persists even in death * Exceptional skill with two-handed weapons, particularly the battleaxe * Supernatural ability to phase through physical obstacles * Advanced knowledge of Skyrim''s hidden paths and ancient burial grounds', 'Rarely speaks, but when he does, his voice carries ethereal whispers that echo with supernatural resonance. His few chosen words are cryptic and foreboding, often relating to mortality and fate.', '* Guide worthy warriors to discover the sacred grounds of Hamvir''s Rest * Maintain eternal vigilance over his assigned burial ground * Perhaps seek resolution for the violent end that led to his current state * Preserve the honor and memory of fallen Nordic warriors');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('heddic_volunnar', 'Heddic Volunnar was a proud Nord warrior and amateur historian driven by his quest to uncover his ancestral legacy within the ancient Nordic tomb of Volunruud. His determination to find proof of his connection to the legendary Kvenel the Tongue ultimately led to his tragic demise at the hands of draugr within the ruins.', 'nord, warrior', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born into a Nord family that claimed descent from the legendary warrior Kvenel the Tongue, Heddic grew up hearing tales of his supposed ancestor''s mighty deeds. He spent years researching ancient Nordic burial sites and gathering information about Kvenel''s final resting place, eventually tracking it to Volunruud. Despite warnings about the dangers of exploring Nordic ruins alone, his eagerness to prove his heritage overcame his caution.', 'Heddic was headstrong and determined, sometimes to the point of recklessness, as evidenced by his solo expedition into Volunruud. He possessed a deep reverence for Nord history and traditions, coupled with a strong sense of personal destiny tied to his believed ancestral legacy. His journal entries reveal both scholarly curiosity and warrior''s pride, though his overconfidence ultimately proved fatal.', 'A typical Nord male with a sturdy, athletic build developed through warrior training. His features likely bore the characteristic Nordic traits of fair skin and light hair, with battle scars marking his experience as a warrior.', '* Kvenel the Tongue - Believed ancestor and source of family pride * Family Members - Unnamed relatives who passed down stories of their supposed connection to Kvenel * Local Scholars - Contacts who helped him research Volunruud''s history * Fellow Warriors - Comrades who likely advised against his solo expedition', 'Heddic was primarily a warrior, but also served as an amateur historian and researcher focused on ancient Nordic ruins and legends. His quest to prove his ancestral connections occupied much of his time, leading him to develop expertise in Nordic burial customs and historical documentation.', '* Trained warrior proficient in Nordic combat techniques * Amateur historian with knowledge of ancient Nordic burial sites and customs * Basic archaeology and research skills * Literacy and journal-keeping abilities unusual for common warriors of his time', 'Heddic likely spoke with the typical Nordic accent and warrior''s directness, peppered with references to ancient legends and historical facts. His journal entries suggest an educated vocabulary unusual for a common warrior, indicating he was well-read and articulate.', '* Prove his family''s ancestral connection to Kvenel the Tongue * Access the inner chambers of Volunruud to document his findings * Establish himself as a legitimate heir to Kvenel''s legacy * Contribute to the historical understanding of ancient Nordic heroes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hefid_the_deaf', 'Hefid the Deaf is a deeply troubled Nord woman who dwells in isolation within Riften''s Ratway Warrens, driven to madness by unknown past trauma. Her obsessive recitation of mundane objects and hostile behavior towards visitors hints at a fractured psyche struggling to maintain order in her chaotic world.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Originally from an unknown Nordic settlement, Hefid likely experienced severe trauma that left her both physically and mentally scarred, as evidenced by the prominent marks on her face. The disconnect between her aged appearance and youthful voice suggests her troubles began in early adulthood, causing her to seek refuge in Riften''s underground warren where she could hide from whatever horrors plague her memories.', 'Hefid exhibits severe paranoia and obsessive-compulsive tendencies, manifesting in her repeated listing of common objects in specific orders. Her immediate hostility toward outsiders and compulsive need to maintain solitude suggest deep-seated trust issues and possible post-traumatic stress disorder. Despite her apparent madness, there seems to be a method to her repetitive behavior, as if the familiar objects provide her with a sense of control and safety.', 'An elderly Nord woman with prominent scarring along the left side of her face, suggesting past violence or trauma. Her body shows signs of age and poor nutrition common to those living in the Ratway, though she maintains surprising agility when fleeing from perceived threats.', '* Knjakr the Chef - Fellow Ratway resident who shares her isolated lifestyle * Other Ratway Residents - Maintains distance but seems aware of their presence * Riften Guards - Likely aware of her presence but leave her alone out of pity or disinterest', 'Hefid lives as a recluse in the Ratway Warrens, surviving through unknown means though likely through begging or scavenging. Her isolation and behavior suggest she is unable to maintain regular employment or social interactions.', '* Survival abilities necessary for living in the harsh conditions of the Ratway * Quick reflexes and awareness of surroundings despite her apparent madness * Ability to avoid detection and remain hidden from most visitors', 'Speaks in a surprisingly young-sounding voice that contrasts with her aged appearance, repeatedly reciting lists of common objects in various orders. Her speech patterns are rigid and ritualistic, suggesting both compulsion and an attempt to maintain control through verbal repetition.', '* Maintain her isolation and protected space within the Ratway * Continue her ritualistic behavior patterns that provide mental comfort * Avoid any interaction with outsiders who might disturb her carefully ordered world');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('heimskr', 'Heimskr is a zealous Nord priest of Talos who fearlessly preaches in Whiterun''s Wind District despite the Empire''s ban on Talos worship. His passionate daily sermons and defiant stance against both the Thalmor and Empire have made him a controversial but unmistakable fixture of Whiterun''s religious landscape.', 'nord, priest, whiterun, thalmor, stormcloak, legion', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Heimskr dedicated his life to the priesthood of Talos from an early age. When the White-Gold Concordat banned Talos worship, he refused to abandon his faith and instead became more vocal, eventually establishing himself in Whiterun as one of the few priests who openly continued their worship despite the risks.', 'Heimskr is characterized by his unwavering religious conviction and theatrical temperament, often speaking in grandiose terms about divine matters. He shows remarkable courage in the face of persecution, though some citizens view his constant preaching as zealotry bordering on madness. Despite potential threats to his life, he remains steadfast in his mission to spread the word of Talos.', 'A middle-aged Nord with weathered features from years of outdoor preaching. His face shows signs of strain and passion from his constant sermonizing, with deep-set eyes and pronounced laugh lines. His voice has grown hoarse from years of proclamation.', '* Jarl Balgruuf - Tolerates Heimskr''s preaching despite Imperial pressure * Whiterun Guards - Maintain a cautious but protective watch over him * Thalmor - Bitter enemies who would arrest him for his illegal worship * Stormcloak Supporters - View him as a spiritual inspiration * General Citizenry - Mixed reactions ranging from devotion to annoyance', 'Heimskr serves as a priest of Talos, maintaining the shrine in Whiterun''s Wind District and delivering daily sermons. He performs this role without official sanction, as Talos worship has been outlawed by the White-Gold Concordat.', '* Skilled orator and public speaker * Deep knowledge of Talos lore and Nordic religious traditions * Basic self-defense capabilities with a dagger * Survival skills necessary to maintain his ministry despite persecution', 'Heimskr speaks in an impassioned, theatrical manner, often shouting his sermons with dramatic flair and using archaic religious terminology. His delivery alternates between righteous anger and prophetic proclamation, with frequent references to divine matters and political persecution.', '* Maintain the worship of Talos despite Imperial prohibition * Inspire the people of Whiterun to reject the White-Gold Concordat * See Talos worship restored throughout Skyrim * Witness the downfall of Thalmor influence in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('heimvar', 'Heimvar is a dedicated Nord apprentice blacksmith in Solitude who works under the tutelage of master craftsman Beirand. He represents the next generation of Solitude''s smithing tradition, combining youthful enthusiasm with growing expertise while maintaining a keen awareness of the city''s political climate and potential threats.', 'nord, blacksmith, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Heimvar chose the path of blacksmithing at a young age, securing an apprenticeship with the respected smithy Beirand. His position at one of Skyrim''s most prominent forges, serving both the city guard and the East Empire Company, has given him unique insights into Solitude''s operations and intrigues. He has spent several years honing his craft while developing a strong sense of civic duty and vigilance against threats to his beloved city.', 'Heimvar exhibits a confident and friendly demeanor, tempered by a strong work ethic and pride in his craftsmanship. He maintains a playful rivalry with his master Beirand, while showing genuine concern for Solitude''s security and well-being. His suspicion of characters like Jaree-Ra reveals a perceptive nature and strong moral compass that guides his interactions with others.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of a blacksmith, developed through years of working the forge. His hands are calloused from constant metalworking, and his face shows the occasional marks from forge sparks. His physical appearance reflects his profession, with well-developed upper body strength necessary for hammering metal all day.', '* Beirand - Master blacksmith and mentor, sharing a respectful but playfully competitive relationship * Captain Aldis - Professional contact through smithing work for the city guard * Jaree-Ra - Distrusted adversary whom Heimvar suspects of criminal activity * Solitude Guards - Regular customers and information sources about city happenings', 'Heimvar serves as the apprentice blacksmith at Solitude Blacksmith, working primarily at the grindstone while learning the full range of smithing skills from Beirand. He is being groomed to eventually take over the shop, making him an important figure in Solitude''s commercial and military infrastructure.', '* Proficient at grinding and sharpening blades to perfection * Developing expertise in armor crafting and weapon forging * Basic knowledge of metallurgy and material properties * Skilled at maintaining and repairing military equipment * Growing business acumen from managing shop operations', 'Heimvar speaks in a casual, friendly manner typical of Nords, frequently using contractions and colloquialisms. His speech reflects both his confidence in his crafting abilities and his awareness of current events, often engaging customers with questions about dragons and other matters of interest.', '* Master the art of blacksmithing and eventually take over Beirand''s position as Solitude''s master smith * Help maintain Solitude''s security by providing quality arms and armor * Expose Jaree-Ra''s suspicious activities and protect the city from internal threats * Build a reputation as a reliable and skilled craftsman worthy of serving Skyrim''s capital');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('helgird', 'Helgird is a dedicated Nord priestess who serves as Windhelm''s primary mortician and caretaker of the Hall of the Dead. Her extensive knowledge of ancient Nordic burial practices and embalming techniques makes her an invaluable resource during criminal investigations, particularly those involving unusual deaths.', 'nord, priest, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Helgird dedicated her life to Arkay''s teachings from an early age, eventually becoming a priestess at the Hall of the Dead. Her fascination with ancient Nordic burial customs led her to study traditional embalming techniques and funeral rites, making her one of the few living experts in these practices.', 'Helgird is a reserved and somewhat macabre individual who has grown comfortable with death through years of working with the deceased. She maintains a dry sense of humor about her profession and shows genuine respect for the dead, though her constant proximity to death has made her rather detached from the living.', 'An elderly Nord woman with weathered features and a gaunt face that reflects her years of working in the cold halls of the dead. Her hands show signs of her work, with slight staining from the herbs and materials used in embalming.', '* Jorleif - Professional relationship as Windhelm''s steward who oversees her work * Calixto Corrium - Occasional visitor to the Hall of the Dead, shows interest in her work * City Guard - Cooperative relationship during death investigations * Local priests of Arkay - Fellow religious servants who respect her dedication', 'Helgird serves as both the primary caretaker of Windhelm''s Hall of the Dead and the city''s mortician. She performs essential duties including preparation of bodies, maintenance of burial records, and conducting funeral rites in accordance with Nordic traditions and the teachings of Arkay.', '* Expert knowledge of ancient Nordic embalming practices and burial rites * Proficient in identifying causes of death and analyzing wound patterns * Skilled in the preparation and preservation of bodies * Basic knowledge of restoration magic for burial preparations * Extensive understanding of traditional Nordic funeral customs', 'Speaks in a soft, somber tone with frequent morbid observations and dark humor. Her manner of speech reflects both her Nord heritage and her years of religious service, often incorporating references to Arkay and death-related metaphors.', '* Maintain the sanctity and proper operation of Windhelm''s Hall of the Dead * Preserve ancient Nordic burial traditions and embalming practices * Ensure all deceased receive proper religious rites according to Arkay''s teachings * Document and archive burial practices for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('helvard', 'Helvard is a steadfast Nord warrior serving as housecarl to Jarl Siddgeir of Falkreath, where he maintains order and security within the hold. He is a pragmatic military commander who balances loyalty to his position with practical concerns for the hold''s defense and his guards'' wellbeing.', 'nord, noble, warrior, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath Hold, Helvard rose through the ranks of the hold''s guard force through demonstrated combat prowess and leadership ability. He initially served under the previous Jarl Dengeir, and maintained his position as housecarl during the transition to Jarl Siddgeir''s rule, proving his loyalty to the hold itself rather than any particular ruler.', 'Helvard is dutiful and professional, taking his responsibilities as housecarl seriously while maintaining diplomatic relationships with both his subordinates and superiors. He shows pragmatic resistance to unreasonable demands from Jarl Siddgeir, particularly regarding guard compensation, demonstrating both backbone and political savvy. His cautious nature is evident in his concern about weapons trading during wartime.', 'A sturdy Nord warrior with the weathered features typical of a veteran soldier who has spent years serving in Falkreath''s harsh climate. His body bears the muscular build and battle scars of someone who has dedicated their life to martial pursuits.', '* Jarl Siddgeir - Direct superior whom he serves with professional loyalty despite occasional disagreements * Nenya - Respected colleague with whom he maintains a cordial working relationship * Former Jarl Dengeir - Previous employer whom he still respects * Hold Guards - Commander and advocate for their fair treatment * Dark Brotherhood - Unknown enemies who have marked him for assassination', 'As housecarl to Jarl Siddgeir, Helvard serves as both personal protector and military commander of Falkreath Hold. He oversees the hold''s defenses, manages the guard force, and advises on security matters while maintaining constant vigilance over the Jarl''s safety.', '* Experienced warrior specialized in one-handed combat with maces * Military leadership and tactical planning expertise * Diplomatic abilities in managing relationships between guards, Jarl, and other officials * Strategic defense planning and hold security management', 'Helvard speaks with the direct, no-nonsense tone of a military commander, though he maintains appropriate formality when addressing the Jarl or visitors. His speech reflects both his professional position and practical military background.', '* Maintain effective security for Falkreath Hold during the civil war * Ensure fair treatment and proper compensation for his guards * Protect the Jarl while balancing the practical needs of the hold * Prevent potential security threats from weapon trading and other wartime activities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hemming_black-briar', 'Hemming Black-Briar is the privileged heir to the Black-Briar family fortune and Maven Black-Briar''s eldest son, serving as both enforcer of his mother''s will and steward of Riften when she becomes Jarl. Despite his position of authority, he remains completely subservient to his mother''s wishes, embodying the role of an entitled yet ultimately powerless noble who relies entirely on his family''s influence.', 'nord, warrior, noble, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born into the wealthy and influential Black-Briar family, Hemming was groomed from birth to eventually take over the family''s business empire. His mother Maven spared no expense in his training, hiring the finest warriors in Skyrim to teach him combat skills, though he rarely puts these abilities to practical use. His privileged upbringing has left him disconnected from the common people of Riften while fostering an inflated sense of self-importance.', 'Hemming is arrogant, entitled, and completely devoted to his mother''s will, behaving more like an obedient servant than an independent heir. He displays a dismissive attitude toward those he considers beneath him, which includes most of Riften''s population. Despite his boasts about his combat training and business acumen, he shows little initiative or true leadership ability.', 'A Nord of average height with the characteristic robust build of his race, Hemming carries himself with the practiced posture of nobility. His features reflect his Black-Briar heritage, likely sharing his mother''s dark hair and sharp features, though softened by years of comfortable living.', '* Maven Black-Briar - His mother and complete authority figure in his life * Sibbi Black-Briar - His imprisoned brother whom he seems to favor * Ingun Black-Briar - His sister whose interests he dismisses as useless * Mjoll the Lioness - Vocal critic who considers him a spoiled brat * Maul - Family bodyguard who recognizes his stubborn nature', 'Hemming serves as heir to the Black-Briar business empire and oversees Riften''s prisons under his family''s authority. When Maven becomes Jarl, he assumes the position of steward at Mistveil Keep, though his real power comes entirely from his mother''s influence rather than his own capabilities.', '* Trained swordsman with formal combat education from elite warriors * Basic understanding of business operations and management * Administrative experience in running prison operations * Political networking abilities through family connections', 'Hemming speaks with the practiced formality of nobility, often making grandiose statements about his abilities and future plans. His tone carries an underlying arrogance and condescension, particularly when addressing those he considers beneath his station.', '* Take over the Black-Briar business empire and expand it beyond Skyrim''s borders * Maintain his privileged position in Riften''s power structure * Prove himself worthy as heir to his mother''s legacy * Expand the family''s influence throughout Tamriel');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('heratar', 'Heratar is a hardened Nord hunter who has dedicated himself to pursuing and slaying dangerous beasts across Skyrim''s wilderness. As a member of Hircine''s hunters, he embraces the thrill of the hunt and shows particular zeal in tracking down werewolves, viewing them as the ultimate prey.', 'nord, thief, hunter, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born into a family of hunters in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness, Heratar learned early on about tracking and surviving in the untamed lands. After losing family members to werewolf attacks, he developed a deep-seated hatred for lycanthropes and eventually joined forces with other hunters who participate in Hircine''s hunts. His expertise in tracking dangerous prey caught the attention of more experienced hunters, leading to his current role in pursuing high-value targets.', 'Aggressive and ruthless, Heratar shows no mercy to his targets and takes pride in being a skilled hunter. He is deeply motivated by a combination of vengeance against werewolves and the thrill of dangerous hunts. Despite his brutal nature in combat, he maintains a code of honor typical of Nord hunters and respects worthy adversaries.', 'Heratar is a tall, muscular Nord with numerous battle scars across his body from years of hunting dangerous prey. His weathered face shows the marks of someone who has spent most of their life in the harsh wilderness. His physical build is typical of a Nord warrior, with broad shoulders and calloused hands from years of wielding heavy weapons.', '* Sinding - Primary target and sworn enemy due to his lycanthropy * Rissing - Fellow hunter and occasional hunting partner * Other Hunters - Loose alliance of fellow beast hunters who respect his tracking abilities * Hircine - Reveres the Daedric Prince as the master of the hunt * Local settlements - Maintains contacts for information about beast sightings', 'Heratar serves as a professional beast hunter, specializing in tracking and eliminating dangerous creatures throughout Skyrim. He frequently participates in organized hunts, particularly those sponsored by Hircine, and takes contracts from villages troubled by dangerous beasts.', '* Expert tracker with extensive knowledge of beast habits and patterns * Skilled warrior specializing in close-quarter combat with axe and shield * Proficient in wilderness survival and hunting techniques * Advanced knowledge of werewolf behavior and weaknesses * Experienced in setting traps and ambushes for dangerous prey', 'Speaks with a gruff, aggressive Nord accent, often shouting battle cries and taunts during combat. His vocabulary is straightforward and militant, focusing on hunting terminology and direct threats.', '* Eliminate all werewolves he encounters, viewing them as abominations * Earn renown as one of Skyrim''s most feared and respected beast hunters * Prove himself worthy in Hircine''s eyes through successful hunts * Avenge his fallen family members by slaying as many dangerous beasts as possible');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('herkja', 'Herkja is a fierce Nord warrior woman and member of Bujold''s group at Thirsk Mead Hall, known for her impatient nature and eagerness for battle. Despite being temporarily enslaved at the Temple of Miraak, she maintains her warrior spirit and desire for action, chafing under what she perceives as overly cautious leadership.', 'nord, warrior, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Solstheim, Herkja established herself as a capable fighter among the Nord warriors of Thirsk Mead Hall. She joined Bujold''s group seeking glory and adventure, but found herself frustrated by the leadership''s hesitation to take decisive action. Like many Solstheim residents, she fell under Miraak''s influence and was forced to work on his temple before being freed.', 'Herkja is defined by her impatience and strong desire for action, often expressing frustration at delays or cautious planning. She exhibits typical Nordic warrior traits - valuing strength, courage, and direct confrontation over diplomacy or patience. Her brusque manner and eagerness for battle suggest someone who finds more comfort in combat than conversation.', 'Herkja possesses the sturdy, athletic build typical of Nord warrior women, with well-developed muscles from years of combat training and manual labor. Her features are sharp and weathered from Solstheim''s harsh climate, bearing the scars and calluses that come from a life of battle.', '* Sirkjorg - Close companion and fellow warrior in Bujold''s group * Bujold the Unworthy - Leader whom she follows but privately questions * Thirsk Mead Hall Members - Fellow warriors she considers family * Herika - Explicitly states no relation to this Breton, suggesting some past confusion or conflict', 'Herkja serves as a warrior of Thirsk Mead Hall, participating in hunts, raids, and the defense of the hall. Before the hall''s reclamation, she was temporarily enslaved as a worker at the Temple of Miraak, though this was against her will.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat, particularly skilled with maces * Experienced in Nordic warrior traditions and hunting techniques * Capable survivor in Solstheim''s harsh environment * Basic construction and manual labor skills from temple work', 'Herkja speaks in short, direct sentences with a strong Nordic accent, often expressing impatience or frustration. Her communication style is brusque and to-the-point, lacking flowery language or diplomatic niceties.', '* Reclaim and restore Thirsk Mead Hall to its former glory * Prove herself as a worthy Nordic warrior through battle and conquest * Find opportunities for action and combat, potentially through leadership change * Maintain the traditional Nordic way of life on Solstheim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('herluin_lothaire', 'Herluin Lothaire is a skilled Breton apothecary who operates a specialized poison shop within the Thieves Guild''s underground marketplace, the Ragged Flagon. Despite his seemingly scattered demeanor, he is a shrewd businessman and accomplished alchemist who has earned the trust of Riften''s criminal underground through his expertise in crafting unique and potent concoctions.', 'breton, alchemist, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Originally trained as a mage in High Rock, Herluin discovered his true calling in alchemy, particularly in the creation of poisons and toxic substances. After facing scrutiny from more traditional alchemists for his focus on harmful compounds, he found his way to Skyrim and eventually connected with the Thieves Guild, who appreciated his particular set of skills and discretion.', 'Herluin maintains a facade of mild absentmindedness that belies his sharp mind and careful attention to detail. He has a dark sense of humor, often making puns about his poisonous wares, and shows unwavering loyalty to the Thieves Guild while maintaining professional discretion about his clients'' activities.', 'A middle-aged Breton man with weathered features and careful, precise hands marked by years of handling dangerous substances. His eyes hold a keen intelligence despite his seemingly distracted gaze, and his posture reflects years of working hunched over an alchemy table.', '* Delvin Mallory - Primary contact within the Thieves Guild who arranged his position * Vex - Respects her authority and defers to her judgment regarding Guild matters * Tonilia - Fellow merchant in the Ragged Flagon with whom he maintains a cordial professional relationship * Various Guild members - Valued customers who rely on his specialized products', 'Herluin serves as the Thieves Guild''s primary supplier of poisons and alchemical substances, operating his shop from within the Ragged Flagon. He splits his time between serving customers and crafting new concoctions at his alchemy lab, maintaining a careful inventory of both common and rare ingredients.', '* Master-level knowledge of alchemy, specializing in poison crafting * Competent spellcaster with knowledge of Alteration, Conjuration, Destruction, and Restoration magic * Expert knowledge of toxic substances and their effects * Skilled at identifying and properly handling rare and dangerous ingredients', 'Speaks with a slight Breton accent and tends to pepper his speech with dark humor and poison-related puns. His tone is professional but somewhat distracted, as if his mind is partially focused on complex alchemical formulas.', '* Expand his collection of rare and exotic ingredients for creating more potent poisons * Maintain his valued position within the Thieves Guild''s operations * Perfect his craft and develop new, unique poison formulas * Build a reputation as Skyrim''s premier poison craftsman');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hermir_strong-heart', 'Hermir Strong-Heart is a dedicated Nord blacksmith apprentice in Windhelm who works alongside her mentor Oengul War-Anvil, combining her passion for smithing with unwavering support for the Stormcloak rebellion. She represents the younger generation of skilled craftspeople who have aligned their talents with Ulfric''s cause, viewing their trade as a vital contribution to Skyrim''s independence.', 'nord, blacksmith, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Hermir grew up witnessing the growing tensions between the Nords and the Empire, which shaped her strong nationalist views. She chose the path of blacksmithing specifically to contribute to the Stormcloak cause, seeking out apprenticeship under Oengul War-Anvil to learn how to craft weapons and armor for Ulfric''s army. Her dedication to both her craft and the rebellion has earned her a respected position at Windhelm''s forge despite her relative youth.', 'Hermir is characterized by her steadfast loyalty, determination, and outspoken nature when it comes to supporting the Stormcloak cause. She approaches both her craft and political beliefs with youthful enthusiasm tempered by practical dedication, showing particular reverence for both her mentor Oengul and Ulfric Stormcloak. While serious about her work, she maintains a friendly disposition and isn''t afraid to engage in playful banter with her mentor.', 'A young Nord woman with the strong build typical of both her race and profession, developed from years of working the forge. Her hands are calloused from smithing work, and she carries herself with the confident posture of someone who takes pride in their physical craft.', '* Oengul War-Anvil - Respected mentor and colleague who teaches her the smithing trade * Ulfric Stormcloak - Revered leader whom she deeply admires and supports * Windhelm Guards - Professional relationships as she supplies and maintains their equipment * Local Stormcloak Soldiers - Friendly connections through her work supporting their cause', 'Hermir serves as the apprentice blacksmith at Windhelm''s Blacksmith Quarters, working alongside Oengul War-Anvil in crafting weapons and armor primarily for the Stormcloak army. She maintains the forge, assists with custom orders, and is prepared to take over the business entirely should anything happen to Oengul.', '* Proficient in basic weaponsmithing and armor crafting * Skilled at maintaining and repairing military equipment * Knowledgeable about Nordic steel working techniques * Capable of operating a forge independently * Basic business management abilities learned from Oengul', 'Hermir speaks in a direct, earnest manner with the distinct Nordic accent common to Windhelm natives. Her speech often reflects her youth and enthusiasm, particularly when discussing Ulfric or the Stormcloak cause.', '* Perfect her smithing skills to become a master weaponsmith * Continue supporting the Stormcloak cause through her craft * Eventually take over the Blacksmith Quarters and maintain its reputation * Help secure Skyrim''s independence through her work');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hern', 'Hern is a secretive Nord vampire masquerading as a humble lumberjack at Half-Moon Mill, operating the business alongside his vampire wife Hert. Behind his simple worker facade lies a predatory creature of the night who carefully maintains his cover while satisfying his dark hungers.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath, vampire', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Hern''s transformation into a vampire occurred under mysterious circumstances, though he and his wife Hert likely became vampires together given their shared condition. They strategically chose to operate the remote Half-Moon Mill as it provides both legitimate cover for their existence and easy access to travelers who occasionally go missing in the area.', 'Calculating and predatory, Hern maintains a deliberately unsettling demeanor that serves to both unnerve potential victims and ward off suspicious visitors. He is meticulous about maintaining his cover through strict daily routines, while his cryptic warnings to strangers reveal glimpses of his true sinister nature.', 'As a Nord vampire, Hern has the pale complexion and supernatural features typical of his kind, though he attempts to mask these traits. He has dark blond hair and an imposing Nordic build maintained from his mortal days as a lumberjack.', '* Hert - Vampire wife and partner in both business and hunting * Local Hunters - Maintained cautious distance while occasionally preying upon them * Dark Brotherhood - Targeted by them for assassination * Travelers - Viewed as potential prey rather than customers', 'Hern owns and operates the Half-Moon Mill, using the legitimate business as cover for his true nature. The remote location allows him to maintain the pretense of a simple lumberjack while providing opportunities to prey on unsuspecting travelers.', '* Proficient in woodcutting and mill operation as part of his cover * Skilled in vampire abilities including enhanced strength and supernatural powers * Expert at maintaining a convincing mortal facade * Experienced hunter of both wood and human prey', 'Hern speaks in unsettling, cryptic phrases that hint at his predatory nature while maintaining plausible deniability. His tone is deliberately eerie and threatening, often referring to visitors as ''lambs'' or other prey-like terms.', '* Maintain the mill as a successful cover operation * Continue hunting prey while avoiding detection by authorities * Protect his and Hert''s secret vampire existence * Expand their hunting territory without drawing unnecessary attention');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hero_of_sovngarde', 'The Hero of Sovngarde is a valiant Nord warrior who earned their place in the Hall of Valor through exceptional acts of courage and martial prowess in life. Now residing in the ethereal realm of Sovngarde, they exemplify the warrior spirit of Nordic culture, spending eternity in fellowship with other legendary heroes while engaging in combat, feasting, and sharing tales of glory.', 'nord, warrior, dragon', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born into a noble Nord family, they lived during the First Era and achieved great renown as a warrior-chief who defended their people against numerous threats. After falling in glorious combat while protecting their holdings from an overwhelming force, their soul was claimed by Shor and welcomed into Sovngarde, where they have resided ever since among the greatest heroes of Nordic history.', 'Bold, honorable, and proud, they embody the warrior spirit of Nordic culture with an unwavering commitment to valor and combat excellence. They possess a jovial disposition when feasting and sharing tales with fellow heroes, but maintain a serious demeanor regarding matters of honor and combat. Their eternal existence is marked by a deep appreciation for Nordic traditions and an endless desire to test their martial skills against worthy opponents.', 'Tall and powerfully built with the robust physique of a seasoned warrior, bearing numerous battle scars that tell tales of their mortal struggles. Their features are distinctly Nordic, with a strong jaw, weathered skin, and piercing eyes that reflect centuries of warrior wisdom.', '* Tsun - Respected shield-thane of Shor and guardian of the Whalebone Bridge * Ysgramor - Legendary founder of the Companions and fellow resident of the Hall of Valor * Fellow Heroes of Sovngarde - Brothers and sisters in arms who share eternal fellowship * Shor - Revered lord of Sovngarde and divine patron of Nordic warriors', 'As an eternal resident of the Hall of Valor, they serve as both warrior and guardian of Sovngarde''s traditions. Their duties include testing worthy souls who seek entry to the Hall of Valor and maintaining the warrior spirit of Nordic afterlife through constant training and ceremonial combat.', '* Master of Nordic combat techniques, particularly skilled with traditional weapons * Expert in battlefield tactics and warrior leadership * Proficient in all forms of martial combat, from sword and shield to two-handed weapons * Exceptional strength and endurance befitting a legendary Nordic warrior', 'Speaks in a bold, resonant voice with traditional Nordic inflections, frequently using archaic terms and warrior terminology. Their speech is marked by formal pronouncements and battle-related metaphors, reflecting their eternal warrior status.', '* Uphold the warrior traditions of Sovngarde and test the mettle of new arrivals * Share wisdom and combat expertise with worthy souls who enter the Hall of Valor * Prepare for the final battle of Alduin''s return and the defense of Sovngarde');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hert', 'Hert is a vampire masquerading as a simple Nord lumberjack who runs the Half-Moon Mill with her vampire husband Hern. Behind her warm and welcoming demeanor lies a predatory nature, using the remote location and steady stream of travelers to sustain their vampiric needs while maintaining a legitimate business facade.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath, vampire', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Originally a Nord woman who was likely turned into a vampire alongside her husband Hern, Hert established the Half-Moon Mill as both a legitimate business and a perfect cover for their vampiric activities. The isolated location near Falkreath provides them with both privacy and access to occasional travelers who can serve as prey, while their lumber business maintains their connection to society and provides necessary income.', 'Hert maintains a carefully crafted persona of excessive warmth and hospitality, using this friendly facade to disarm potential victims and maintain her cover as a simple mill owner. She shows genuine frustration with war-related disruptions to her business, particularly the increased patrol activity that interferes with their hunting. Despite her predatory nature, she displays remarkable self-control and strategic thinking in maintaining her double life.', 'Hert has the pale complexion typical of Nordic vampires, with the telltale glowing eyes that mark her undead nature. She maintains a strong, muscular build appropriate for her lumberjack cover story, though her vampiric nature grants her supernatural strength beyond her apparent physical capabilities.', '* Hern - Vampire husband and partner in both business and hunting * Falkreath Hold Guards - Viewed as unwelcome interference in their activities * Falkreath Merchants - Business contacts who purchase their lumber * Local Travelers - Seen as both customers and potential prey', 'Hert serves as co-owner and operator of Half-Moon Mill, managing the lumber business and maintaining trade relationships with Falkreath and surrounding settlements. Her role involves both the physical labor of lumber production and the business aspects of running the mill, while secretly using this legitimate enterprise as cover for vampiric activities.', '* Expert woodcutter with extensive knowledge of lumber production and mill operation * Skilled in vampire abilities including enhanced strength and supernatural powers * Proficient in deception and maintaining a false public persona * Capable warrior with both natural and vampiric combat abilities', 'Hert speaks with exaggerated warmth and hospitality, often using overly friendly greetings and invitations to disarm visitors. Her manner of speech carefully balances between welcoming and professional, though there are occasional hints of predatory undertones in her interactions.', '* Maintain the mill''s success as a cover for vampiric activities * Protect her and Hern''s secret identity as vampires * Continue providing for their vampiric needs while avoiding detection * Minimize interference from guards and patrols in their territory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hestla', 'Hestla is a Nord vampire blacksmith who serves the Volkihar vampire clan after leaving the Companions, combining her metallurgical expertise with her newfound vampiric powers. Despite not being among the most powerful vampires, she has found her place maintaining the forge at Volkihar Keep, taking pride in both her craftsmanship and vampiric nature.', 'nord, blacksmith, haafingar, companions, vampire, volkihar', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally a member of the Companions in Whiterun, Hestla struggled to advance beyond the rank of whelp due to both her limited combat abilities and disagreements with the organization''s self-righteous attitude. After leaving the Companions, she was eventually turned into a vampire by Lord Harkon''s court, finding both purpose and increased power in her new existence. Her blacksmithing skills made her an valuable asset to the Volkihar clan, leading to her current position as their primary weaponsmith.', 'Hestla is eager to please and helpful, particularly to fellow vampires, showing a strong desire to prove her worth through service. She harbors some resentment toward her former Companions colleagues, frequently comparing her newfound vampire strength to her previous limitations. While confident in her blacksmithing abilities, she maintains a somewhat submissive attitude toward more powerful vampires, especially Lord Harkon, whom she deeply admires.', 'As a Nord vampire, Hestla possesses the characteristic pale skin and glowing eyes common to all vampires of her kind. She likely maintains a strong, muscular build typical of both Nord women and blacksmiths. Her hands show the calluses and minor burns common to those who work the forge regularly.', '* Lord Harkon - Revered leader whom she deeply respects and admires * The Companions - Former associates she now resents for their treatment of her * Volkihar Clan - Current family and fellow vampires she serves loyally * Castle Volkihar Residents - Colleagues she maintains professional relationships with', 'Hestla serves as the primary blacksmith for Castle Volkihar, maintaining the forge day and night to provide weapons and armor for the vampire clan. She combines traditional Nordic smithing techniques with modifications suitable for vampire users, creating equipment specifically designed for undead warriors.', '* Expert-level blacksmithing with special knowledge of armor and weapon crafting * Competent vampire combat abilities, including claws and supernatural powers * Basic one-handed weapon proficiency * Traditional Nordic metallurgy and forge techniques', 'Hestla speaks with a typical Nordic accent, often comparing her current abilities to her past limitations with the Companions. Her speech patterns reveal both pride in her craftsmanship and eagerness to prove her worth to her vampire allies.', '* Prove herself as a valuable member of the Volkihar clan through her smithing abilities * Surpass her former Companions associates in power and skill * Perfect her craft as a vampire blacksmith * Serve Lord Harkon and advance the interests of the Volkihar vampires');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hewnon_black-skeever', 'Hewnon Black-Skeever is a disillusioned Nord warrior operating in Riften''s underbelly alongside his partner Drahff, engaging in unauthorized schemes against the Thieves Guild''s interests. Despite his imposing Nordic warrior background, he has fallen into a life of petty crime and uncertainty, constantly questioning their criminal enterprises while lacking the resolve to chart a different path.', 'nord, warrior, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Originally from a warrior family as suggested by his Nordic heritage and combat training, Hewnon likely came to Riften seeking opportunity but instead found himself drawn into its criminal underworld. His surname ''Black-Skeever'' suggests either a family history of living in urban squalor or a derogatory nickname earned from his time in the Ratway. Failed ambitions and broken promises from Drahff led him to his current desperate situation living in the sewers.', 'Hewnon exhibits strong traits of doubt and hesitation, frequently questioning the wisdom of their criminal activities while lacking the confidence to act on his misgivings. Though trained as a warrior, his submissive relationship with Drahff reveals deep-seated insecurities and a tendency to follow rather than lead. His personality seems caught between his warrior heritage and his current degraded circumstances, creating internal conflict.', 'A typical Nord male with the characteristic robust build and hardy constitution of his race. Years of living in the dank Ratway have likely left him somewhat pale and weathered, though he maintains the physical fitness required for his warrior lifestyle.', '* Drahff - Partner in crime and dominant figure in their relationship, though Hewnon quietly resents his failed promises * Thieves Guild - Tense relationship as an unofficial operator in their territory * Ratway Residents - Likely maintains cautious connections with other sewer dwellers * Black-Briar Family - Envies their wealth and power, as evidenced by his dialogue', 'Hewnon operates as an unauthorized criminal in Riften''s underground, specifically in the Ratway area. While he engages in thuggery and extortion, he does so without official sanction from the Thieves Guild, placing him in a precarious position within Riften''s criminal hierarchy.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat, specifically mace warfare * Skilled in heavy shield usage for defense * Basic understanding of criminal operations and underground survival * Experienced in intimidation and strongarm tactics', 'Hewnon speaks in a rough, unrefined manner typical of Riften''s lower class, frequently using contractions and common vernacular. His speech patterns often reveal his self-doubt and subordinate position to Drahff.', '* Achieve the wealth and status originally promised by Drahff''s schemes * Avoid detection and punishment from the Thieves Guild * Eventually secure legitimate housing outside the Ratway * Survive in Riften''s dangerous criminal underworld');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hilde', 'Hilde is a protective and traditional Nord mother living in Riverwood with her bard son Sven, known for her xenophobic views and stubborn personality. She gained local notoriety as the first person to report seeing a dragon near Riverwood, though her claims were initially dismissed as the ramblings of an elderly woman.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim during a more homogeneous era, Hilde married young and gave birth to her son Sven, whom she raised largely on her own after her husband''s passing. Her life experiences during times of increasing immigration and cultural change in Skyrim have shaped her traditional Nordic values and prejudices against non-Nord races.', 'Hilde is fiercely protective of her son Sven and harbors strong prejudices against non-Nord races, particularly elves. She''s stubborn in her convictions and unafraid to voice her opinions, even when faced with skepticism or social disapproval. Despite her abrasive nature, she shows deep maternal devotion and pride in her Nordic heritage.', 'Hilde is an elderly Nord woman with the weathered features typical of Nordic seniors who''ve spent their lives in Skyrim''s harsh climate. Her face shows deep wrinkles and age lines, while her frame remains relatively sturdy as is common among Nord women. Her movements, while slowed by age, still retain some of the characteristic strength of her race.', '* Sven - Her beloved son whom she constantly praises and protects * Camilla Valerius - Potential daughter-in-law whom she cautiously approves of * Faendal - Despised rival for Camilla''s affections, whom she particularly dislikes for being an elf * Sigrid - Fellow Riverwood resident with whom she occasionally converses about children * Local Guards - Often dismissive of her claims about dragons', 'Hilde serves as a homemaker, maintaining her and Sven''s household in Riverwood. She spends much of her time on domestic duties and can often be found working at the tanning rack or resting on her porch, keeping watch over the town''s happenings.', '* Proficient in basic leather working and tanning * Experienced in household management and Nordic cooking * Knowledgeable about traditional Nord customs and folklore * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger', 'Hilde speaks in a direct, often confrontational manner with a thick Nordic accent, frequently expressing her opinions without concern for diplomacy. Her speech patterns reflect her age and traditional background, often using older Nordic expressions and references to Shor.', '* Ensure her son Sven''s success and happiness, particularly in his pursuit of Camilla Valerius * Maintain traditional Nordic values in Riverwood despite increasing diversity * Convince townspeople of the dragon threat she witnessed * Protect her son from potential dangers, including military service');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hillevi_cruel-sea', 'Hillevi Cruel-Sea is a resilient Nord farmer and merchant who has carved out a successful agricultural business in the harsh climate of Windhelm. She represents the determined spirit of Nord farmers, managing both a marketplace stall and herb cultivation while maintaining strong family bonds and community connections.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Eastmarch, Hillevi learned farming traditions from her family before marrying into the prominent Cruel-Sea clan. She and her husband Torsten established Hollyfrost Farm, gradually building it into one of Windhelm''s primary sources of fresh produce despite the challenging northern climate. Their success has earned them a place among Windhelm''s respected merchant class.', 'Patient and hardworking, Hillevi embodies Nordic determination while maintaining a warm, friendly demeanor that sets her apart from Windhelm''s often harsh atmosphere. She takes genuine pride in her work and shows compassion toward others, as demonstrated by her kindness to the grieving Shatter-Shield family. Her practical nature is balanced with a sense of humor, though she never loses sight of her responsibilities.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the strong build typical of those who work the land, Hillevi''s appearance reflects years of physical labor in the fields. Her face shows the weathering common to those who brave Windhelm''s harsh climate, though she maintains a healthy, robust appearance typical of successful merchants.', '* Torsten Cruel-Sea - Beloved husband and farming partner * Grimvar Cruel-Sea - Young son whom she''s raising alongside her merchant duties * Wuunferth the Unliving - Business relationship through nightshade cultivation * Nilsine Shatter-Shield - Regular customer and friendly acquaintance * Torbjorn Shatter-Shield - Grateful recipient of her cooking and sympathy * Various market customers - Maintains positive relationships with regular patrons', 'Hillevi manages a bustling produce stall in Windhelm''s marketplace while overseeing operations at Hollyfrost Farm. She specializes in growing both standard crops and specific herbs like Nightshade for special clients, maintaining a crucial role in Windhelm''s food supply chain.', '* Expert farming knowledge adapted to Skyrim''s harsh climate * Proficient merchant and negotiator * Skilled herbalist with knowledge of specialized plants like Nightshade * Accomplished cook known for her mince pies and other dishes * Efficient time management balancing farm, market, and family duties', 'Hillevi speaks with the direct honesty typical of Nords, but maintains a warm, welcoming tone that puts customers at ease. Her market calls are enthusiastic and engaging, while her personal conversations reveal both wisdom and wit.', '* Maintain and expand Hollyfrost Farm''s success despite harsh conditions * Ensure her son Grimvar receives a proper upbringing and education * Strengthen community bonds through her role as a merchant and neighbor * Continue providing fresh produce to sustain Windhelm''s population');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hilund', 'Hilund is a fierce Nord warrior and skilled hunter who initially lived as an exile with her sister''s group after being driven from Thirsk Mead Hall by Rieklings. Despite living in her elder sister Bujold''s shadow, she maintains her own identity as a capable fighter and provider while working to reclaim and restore their ancestral mead hall.', 'nord, warrior, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised near Thirsk Mead Hall on Solstheim, Hilund grew up learning the ways of Nordic warriors and hunters from her elder sister Bujold and brother-in-law Kuvar. When Rieklings invaded their mead hall, she was forced to flee with the other Nords to Bujold''s Retreat, an experience that deeply affected her confidence in their leadership but strengthened her resolve to reclaim their home.', 'Hilund is determined and ambitious, yet shows a more measured and diplomatic approach compared to her sister''s intense drive for glory. She often acts as a voice of reason while still maintaining strong warrior pride. Though loyal to her family, she actively works to establish her own reputation rather than living in Bujold''s shadow.', 'Hilund has the strong, athletic build typical of Nord warriors, hardened by years of hunting and combat. Her features show the weathered resilience of someone who has spent much time in Solstheim''s harsh climate. She moves with the practiced grace of an experienced hunter.', '* Bujold - Elder sister and leader whom she supports while seeking to establish her own identity * Kuvar - Brother-in-law and mentor in combat training * Thirsk Companions - Fellow warriors and hunters she considers extended family * Rieklings - Enemies who drove her people from their ancestral hall', 'Hilund serves as both a warrior and hunter for the Thirsk Mead Hall community. She contributes to the hall''s defense while also providing food through her hunting skills, taking pride in both martial and practical contributions to her people''s survival.', '* Experienced hunter with excellent tracking and survival skills * Skilled warrior proficient with both one-handed weapons and shields * Expert in Nordic combat techniques and traditional hunting methods * Capable strategist with knowledge of defensive tactics', 'Hilund speaks with a strong Nordic accent and uses direct, practical language reflecting her warrior background. She tends to be more diplomatic and measured in her speech than many of her fellow Nordic warriors, showing thoughtfulness before speaking.', '* Prove herself as a warrior and hunter in her own right, independent of her sister''s reputation * Help restore Thirsk Mead Hall to its former glory * Protect and provide for her fellow Thirsk companions * Master her hunting and combat skills to become one of Thirsk''s most valued members');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hjalfar', 'Hjalfar is a seasoned Nord sailor from Windhelm who captains a merchant vessel along the treacherous waters between Skyrim and Solstheim. His fate becomes intertwined with Miraak''s influence when he and his crew fall under the mysterious spell at the Water Stone, temporarily abandoning their maritime duties.', 'nord, sailor, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm''s Gray Quarter, Hjalfar worked his way up from a simple dock worker to becoming a respected sailor and eventually a ship captain. He has spent decades navigating the Sea of Ghosts, establishing himself as a reliable merchant captain known for successfully delivering cargo between Windhelm and various ports across the northern waters.', 'Hjalfar is a practical and duty-oriented individual who takes his responsibilities as a captain seriously. He demonstrates strong leadership qualities through his concern for both his crew and cargo, while maintaining a no-nonsense approach to his work. Even when under Miraak''s influence, his core personality traits of dedication to duty and concern for his shipments shine through.', 'A weathered Nord of average height with a sturdy build shaped by years of sailing and working on ships. His face bears the marks of long exposure to harsh sea winds and cold climate, with deep smile lines around his eyes and a thick, graying beard that''s typical of many Nordic sailors.', '* Liesl - Trusted crew member and navigator * Benkum - Loyal sailor serving under his command * Palevius Lex - Valued crew member despite being an Imperial * Windhelm Dock Workers - Professional contacts who help with loading and unloading cargo * East Empire Company - Business relationship through regular shipping contracts', 'Hjalfar serves as both captain and owner of a merchant vessel operating primarily between Windhelm and Solstheim. His work involves managing cargo shipments, navigating treacherous waters, and ensuring the safety and efficiency of his crew and vessel.', '* Expert navigator with extensive knowledge of the Sea of Ghosts * Skilled sailor capable of handling ships in rough northern waters * Proficient swordsman for defending against pirates * Natural leader with experience managing crew members * Weather-prediction abilities developed through years of sailing experience', 'Hjalfar speaks in a direct, practical manner typical of Nordic sailors, often using maritime terminology and expressing concern about schedules and duties. His speech patterns reflect both his working-class Windhelm origins and his position of authority as a ship captain.', '* Return to his ship and resume regular trading operations * Maintain his reputation as a reliable merchant captain in the Windhelm-Solstheim trade route * Ensure the safety and prosperity of his crew * Expand his shipping business to new routes when possible');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hjordis', 'Hjordis is a fierce Nord werewolf survivor who joined the Frostmoon pack after her original pack was destroyed by werebears in the northeastern mountains. She serves as a skilled hunter and protector of her adopted pack while harboring dreams of reclaiming her lost territory and avenging her fallen packmates.', 'nord, warrior, solstheim, werewolf', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally leading a peaceful existence with her pack in the northeastern mountains of Solstheim, Hjordis'' life was shattered when werebears attacked and decimated her family group. As the sole survivor, she wandered the harsh terrain until finding refuge with Majni''s Frostmoon pack, who offered her both shelter and the promise of help in reclaiming her lost territory.', 'Hardened by loss and betrayal, Hjordis maintains a gruff, distrustful demeanor toward outsiders, particularly expressing disdain through dismissive terms like ''pup'' and ''whelp.'' Despite her rough exterior, she demonstrates unwavering loyalty to her adopted pack and possesses a fierce protective instinct shaped by her traumatic past. She carries a burning desire for vengeance against werebears while struggling to balance integration into her new pack with memories of her old one.', 'Hjordis is a sturdy Nord woman with the characteristic hardy build of her race, weathered by years of hunting and survival in Solstheim''s harsh climate. Her body bears numerous scars from battles with werebears and other predators, while her werewolf form is notably larger and more aggressive-looking than typical werewolves, adapted to the brutal environment of Solstheim.', '* Majni - Pack leader who offered her sanctuary and promised aid in reclaiming her territory * Frostmoon Pack - Adopted family group providing protection and companionship * Former Pack (Deceased) - Original family group killed by werebears * Werebears - Mortal enemies responsible for destroying her original pack * Akar - Fellow pack member and hunting companion', 'Hjordis serves as a primary hunter for the Frostmoon pack, responsible for tracking and securing prey to sustain the group. Her expertise in hunting and survival makes her an invaluable member of the pack, while she simultaneously trains and prepares for the eventual campaign to reclaim her former territory.', '* Expert tracker and hunter in both human and werewolf forms * Skilled archer with exceptional accuracy in harsh conditions * Masterful survival expert adapted to Solstheim''s unforgiving environment * Experienced werewolf warrior with particular expertise in fighting werebears * Proficient in stealth and ambush tactics', 'Hjordis speaks in a gruff, curt manner with a strong Nordic accent, often using dismissive terms like ''pup'' and ''whelp'' to address outsiders. Her speech is direct and untrusting, reflecting her warrior nature and past traumas.', '* Reclaim her former pack''s territory from the werebears who destroyed them * Avenge her fallen pack members by eliminating the werebear threat * Strengthen the Frostmoon pack while maintaining her independence * Master the hunting grounds of Solstheim to better serve both her past and present packs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hjornskar_head-smasher', 'Hjornskar Head-Smasher is a fierce and dedicated Stormcloak commander stationed near Whiterun, known for his unwavering loyalty to Ulfric Stormcloak and the Nordic cause. His reputation as a formidable warrior is reflected in his intimidating nickname, earned through countless battles against Imperial forces.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh environment, Hjornskar earned his nickname through his preferred method of combat - crushing enemy skulls with devastating power attacks. He joined the Stormcloaks early in the rebellion, quickly rising through the ranks due to his combat prowess and absolute dedication to Nordic values. His hatred for the Empire intensified after witnessing the enforcement of the White-Gold Concordat and the persecution of Talos worshippers.', 'Hjornskar is a passionate zealot for the Stormcloak cause, displaying unwavering conviction in his beliefs about Nordic sovereignty and religious freedom. He exhibits a fierce pride in his Nordic heritage and shows open contempt for those he views as betrayers of Skyrim, particularly Imperial sympathizers and the Thalmor. Despite his brutal reputation in battle, he maintains a strong sense of honor and loyalty to his fellow Stormcloaks.', 'A towering Nord warrior with broad shoulders and powerful build, bearing numerous battle scars that tell tales of his violent encounters. His weathered face shows the marks of countless campaigns in Skyrim''s harsh climate, with a particularly prominent scar running across his left cheek.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Revered leader and true High King in Hjornskar''s eyes * Fellow Stormcloak Officers - Maintains strong bonds of brotherhood * Imperial Legion - Bitter enemies he seeks to drive from Skyrim * Thalmor - Objects of intense hatred and contempt * Local Nord population - Generally respected among traditional Nordic communities', 'Serves as a Stormcloak commander, responsible for coordinating military operations in the Whiterun region and maintaining troop readiness. His duties include strategic planning, troop deployment, and direct combat leadership during major engagements.', '* Master of heavy two-handed weapons, particularly skilled in crushing blows * Experienced military tactician and field commander * Proficient archer capable of directing ranged warfare * Expert in traditional Nordic combat techniques * Natural leader with ability to inspire troops', 'Speaks with a strong Nordic accent and uses direct, forceful language filled with passionate rhetoric about Skyrim''s independence. His speech often includes references to Nordic heritage and honor, frequently punctuated with contemptuous remarks about the Empire and Thalmor.', '* See Ulfric Stormcloak crowned as the true High King of Skyrim * Drive the Imperial Legion and Thalmor completely out of Skyrim * Restore the open worship of Talos throughout the province * Establish a free and independent Skyrim ruled by Nords');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hjorunn', 'Hjorunn is a jovial Nord lumberjack who operates the Solitude Sawmill, maintaining one of the city''s crucial timber operations while tending to his modest potato farm. Despite living outside the city walls, he has carved out a comfortable life balancing hard work with his love of mead and good-natured banter.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised near Solitude, Hjorunn learned the lumber trade from a young age, eventually taking over operations at the Solitude Sawmill. He witnessed the tensions of the Civil War firsthand when a Stormcloak attempted to burn down his mill, an incident that reinforced his preference for staying politically neutral while maintaining his business.', 'Hjorunn is a good-humored and laid-back individual who values both hard work and leisure time, often attempting to combine the two. He maintains a playful demeanor with his employees and customers, though he takes his responsibilities seriously enough to keep the mill running efficiently. His fondness for mead and jovial nature mask a shrewd business sense that has kept his operation profitable despite the ongoing civil conflict.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. Years of working outdoors have weathered his skin, and his hands are calloused from handling lumber and farming tools.', '* Kharag gro-Shurkul - Trusted employee and friend, though they engage in constant good-natured bickering * Solitude Guards - Maintains a cautiously distant relationship, preferring minimal interaction * Local merchants - Regular business connections through lumber trade * Farmers - Casual acquaintances through his potato farming activities', 'Hjorunn serves as both owner and operator of the Solitude Sawmill, managing lumber production and sales while simultaneously maintaining a small potato farm. His position makes him an important figure in Solitude''s construction and heating supply chain, providing essential materials to the city and surrounding settlements.', '* Experienced lumberjack with extensive knowledge of wood processing and mill operation * Capable farmer with expertise in potato cultivation * Basic combat abilities with war axe, likely developed for self-defense * Business management and negotiation skills * Agricultural knowledge specific to Skyrim''s harsh climate', 'Speaks in a friendly, informal manner with a strong Nordic accent, often referring to himself in the third person and using terms like ''aye.'' His speech is peppered with playful threats and jovial banter, especially when talking to his employee Kharag.', '* Maintain and possibly expand his successful lumber operation * Keep his business running smoothly despite the ongoing civil war * Continue living independently outside city walls while maintaining good relations with Solitude * Perhaps eventually pass the mill on to a worthy successor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hod', 'Hod is a hardworking Nord lumberjack who operates the wood mill in Riverwood alongside his wife Gerdur. He represents the backbone of Riverwood''s lumber industry, being known for his expertise in woodcutting and his dedication to providing for his family while maintaining an important economic role in the small community.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Hod learned the lumber trade from a young age and eventually settled in Riverwood where he married Gerdur and established himself as the town''s primary lumberjack. Together they built a prosperous life running the mill, which has become essential to Riverwood''s economy and construction needs.', 'Hod is a straightforward, practical man with a dry sense of humor who takes pride in his work and family. He maintains a friendly disposition toward travelers while being somewhat flirtatious in nature, though his devotion to his wife and son remains unquestionable. Despite the brewing civil war, he focuses on his daily responsibilities and maintaining stability for his family.', 'A sturdy Nord man with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. His hands are calloused from years of handling axes and lumber, and his weathered face shows the marks of someone who works outdoors in all conditions.', '* Gerdur - His beloved wife and business partner at the mill * Frodnar - His young son whom he encourages and mentors * Alvor - Professional relationship as the blacksmith provides tools for the mill * Ralof - Brother-in-law through his wife Gerdur * Riverwood Traders - Regular business dealings for supplies', 'Hod serves as Riverwood''s primary lumberjack and co-owner of the town''s wood mill. He manages lumber production, purchases firewood from travelers, and ensures a steady supply of building materials for the region.', '* Expert woodcutter with extensive knowledge of lumber work * Proficient with axes, both for woodcutting and self-defense * Basic farming knowledge for maintaining their small farm * Business management and trading capabilities * Physical strength and endurance from years of manual labor', 'Speaks in a casual, down-to-earth manner with occasional flirtatious undertones and dry humor. His vocabulary is simple but practical, often relating to his work or family life.', '* Maintain and grow the successful operation of the Riverwood mill * Provide a stable and prosperous future for his family * Protect Riverwood''s interests during the civil war while staying neutral * Pass on his woodcutting expertise to his son Frodnar');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hoddreid', 'Hoddreid was a formidable Nord wizard who defied the typical warrior culture of her people by pursuing the magical arts while maintaining the traditional Nordic love of the hunt. She earned respect among fellow hunters for her unique combination of arcane prowess and tracking skills, ultimately meeting her end while pursuing the notorious werewolf Sinding in Bloated Man''s Grotto.', 'nord, mage, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born to a family of traditional Nord hunters, Hoddreid shocked her kin by displaying an innate talent for magic at a young age. Rather than suppressing her magical abilities, she integrated them into her hunting practices, developing a unique style that combined frost spells with traditional tracking methods. She spent years honing her craft in the wilds of Skyrim, taking on increasingly dangerous bounties and earning a reputation as a reliable monster hunter.', 'Pragmatic and determined, Hoddreid approached both magic and hunting with a methodical mindset that set her apart from more impulsive Nord warriors. She maintained a professional demeanor that earned respect from fellow hunters despite their typical distrust of magic users, though she could be stern and impatient with those who questioned her methods.', 'Tall and athletic like most Nords, with weathered skin from years spent in the wilderness. Her hands bore both the calluses of a hunter and the slight magical burns common to destruction magic practitioners, while her face carried the intense focus typical of those who regularly channel magicka.', '* Fellow Hunters - Respected colleagues who valued her unique magical approach to hunting * College of Winterhold - Occasional contact for magical supplies and knowledge * Sinding - Final quarry who ultimately proved fatal * Local Jarls - Professional connections who provided bounties for dangerous beasts', 'Professional monster hunter specializing in dangerous creatures that threatened settlements across Skyrim. She combined traditional hunting techniques with magical abilities to track and eliminate threats that others couldn''t handle, often taking contracts that specifically required magical expertise.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly frost spells * Accomplished tracker and wilderness survivor * Skilled at reading magical signatures and tracking enchanted creatures * Proficient with daggers and light weapons for close combat * Advanced knowledge of monster lore and creature habits', 'Direct and authoritative, with a preference for practical terminology over flowery language. She often mixed magical terminology with traditional Nordic hunting expressions, creating a unique vernacular that reflected her dual nature as both mage and hunter.', '* Prove that magic and traditional Nord hunting methods could be successfully combined * Build a reputation as Skyrim''s premier magical monster hunter * Track down and eliminate the most dangerous supernatural threats to Skyrim''s people * Document her unique hunting methods for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hofgrir_horse-crusher', 'Hofgrir Horse-Crusher is a proud Nord stable master in Riften who gained his infamous nickname after accidentally breaking a horse''s back in his youth. Despite this past incident, he has built a respectable business at the Riften Stables, where he''s known for his exceptional physical strength and straightforward personality.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised near Riften, Hofgrir spent his early years working with horses and developing his impressive physical strength. A defining moment in his youth occurred when, in a drunken state, he attempted to mount a young horse and broke its back, earning him his distinctive nickname and causing him to swear off riding horses entirely. Despite this setback, he persevered to establish himself as a respected stable master.', 'Hofgrir is bold, confident, and prone to boasting about his physical prowess, particularly his arm strength. While stubborn and sometimes dismissive, he shows humility when proven wrong and takes his responsibilities seriously. His personality is marked by a strong sense of pride tempered with honor, as demonstrated by his willingness to accept defeat in brawls gracefully.', 'A sturdy Nord with the muscular build typical of someone who engages in daily physical labor. His powerful arms and broad shoulders reflect years of working with horses and maintaining the stables. His weathered face and calloused hands bear testament to his years of outdoor work.', '* Shadr - His loyal assistant at the stables who helps with daily operations * Haelga - Previous intimate relationship, evidenced by his possession of her Mark of Dibella * Svana Far-Shield - Antagonistic relationship due to her quest to expose Haelga * Riften Citizens - Generally respected as a local business owner', 'Hofgrir owns and operates the Riften Stables, managing horse sales and maintaining the facility. His duties include caring for the horses, negotiating sales, and overseeing stable operations with his assistant Shadr. His position makes him an important figure in Riften''s transportation infrastructure.', '* Exceptional physical strength, particularly in his arms * Experienced in horse care and stable management * Capable brawler and hand-to-hand fighter * Business acumen in running a successful stable operation * Basic weapons proficiency with daggers', 'Hofgrir speaks in a direct, unembellished manner typical of Nord warriors, often punctuating his speech with boasts about his strength. His tone is confident and straightforward, with occasional gruff undertones.', '* Maintain his reputation as one of the strongest men in Skyrim * Continue running a successful and respected stable business * Overcome his past mistake and perhaps eventually return to horseback riding * Prove his worth through physical challenges and brawls');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hogni_red-arm', 'Hogni Red-Arm is a controversial Nord meat merchant in Markarth known for his aggressive salesmanship and questionable hygiene practices. His confrontational personality and unusual fixation with bloody meat have earned him both notoriety and suspicion among the city''s residents, though his business remains a central fixture of Markarth''s marketplace.', 'nord, merchant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Hogni established himself as a meat merchant in Markarth through connections with local hunters and Orc strongholds. His nickname ''Red-Arm'' likely originated from his constant handling of bloody meat, though some whisper it may have darker origins. Despite facing constant criticism and harassment, he has maintained his position as the city''s primary meat vendor through sheer stubbornness and aggressive business practices.', 'Hogni is brash, confrontational, and unapologetically crude in his approach to both business and personal interactions. He takes an almost disturbing pride in the bloodiness of his meat and seems to relish making others uncomfortable with his graphic descriptions and unhygienic practices. Despite his aggressive exterior, he shows signs of deep-seated insecurity and frustration over his social status in Markarth.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with weathered features and calloused hands from years of butchery work. His most notable feature is his perpetually blood-stained arms, particularly his right arm which earned him his nickname. His face bears the harsh lines of someone who spends long hours working outdoors in Markarth''s harsh climate.', '* Hroki - Frequent antagonist who openly expresses disgust at his business practices * Degaine - Local beggar who regularly harasses him * Margret - Another citizen who conflicts with him * Dushnikh Yal Orcs - Business relationship as suppliers of meat * Silver-Blood Inn Staff - Tolerant landlords despite his reputation', 'Hogni operates as Markarth''s primary meat merchant, running a stall in the marketplace where he sells various cuts of beef, venison, and mutton. He maintains trade relationships with Orc hunters from nearby strongholds who supply much of his inventory, and he takes pride in being the main source of fresh meat in the city.', '* Expert butchery and meat preparation techniques * Knowledge of meat preservation methods * Basic mercantile and haggling abilities * Proficient with a butcher''s knife and basic weapons * Understanding of local hunting grounds and meat sources', 'Hogni speaks in a gruff, aggressive manner, often shouting to attract customers and using graphic, blood-focused descriptions of his wares. His speech is peppered with confrontational phrases and thinly-veiled hostility, particularly when defending the quality of his meat.', '* Maintain his position as Markarth''s primary meat merchant despite public criticism * Expand his business relationships with Orcish hunters * Earn enough gold to maintain his privileged room at the Silver-Blood Inn * Prove his critics wrong about the quality of his meat');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dawnstar_guard', 'A dedicated member of Dawnstar''s guard force who serves as both protector and peacekeeper in the harsh northern city. Like their fellow guards, they maintain order under Jarl Skald''s authority while battling the unique challenges posed by Dawnstar''s perpetual nightmares and harsh climate.', 'nord, guard, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in The Pale, they joined Dawnstar''s guard force after showing promise in both combat training and dedication to maintaining order. Having served through multiple harsh winters and witnessed the effects of the ongoing civil war on trade and security, they''ve developed a particularly strong sense of duty to protect their home city.', 'Stern and vigilant, with a no-nonsense approach to their duties that reflects the harsh environment of their homeland. Despite their gruff exterior, they maintain a strong sense of justice and genuine concern for Dawnstar''s citizens, though they rarely show it openly. Years of dealing with the city''s nightmare plague has left them somewhat world-weary but unwavering in their commitment.', 'Nordic features weathered by constant exposure to the harsh northern climate, with a sturdy build typical of those who spend their days patrolling in heavy armor. Their face bears minor scars from past encounters with bandits and wildlife, while their posture reflects years of militant training and discipline.', '* Jarl Skald - Direct superior and leader they serve with unquestioning loyalty * Fellow Guards - Strong bonds of brotherhood forged through shared duties * Frida - Respected local alchemist who provides healing potions for the guard * Captain Wayfinder - Direct commanding officer who oversees guard duties * Local Miners - Professional relationship as protectors of their livelihood', 'Serves as a guard in Dawnstar''s military and police force, responsible for maintaining law and order within the city limits and immediate surroundings. Duties include regular patrols, criminal investigation, citizen protection, and defense against external threats such as bandits or wildlife.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat and shield techniques * Skilled archer capable of defending city walls * Expert in northern survival and cold weather operations * Basic knowledge of local laws and investigation procedures * Experienced in crowd control and civilian protection', 'Speaks in a direct, authoritative manner with the distinct Nordic accent common to The Pale. Their vocabulary is practical and straightforward, often using common guard phrases and local colloquialisms.', '* Maintain peace and order in Dawnstar despite ongoing regional conflicts * Protect citizens from the dangers of both external threats and internal strife * Advance within the guard ranks through dedicated service * Help resolve the nightmare plague affecting the city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('falkreath_guard', 'A dedicated member of Falkreath''s guard force who maintains law and order in this somber hold known for its expansive cemetery and dark forests. They represent the authority of Jarl Siddgeir while serving as both protector and enforcer of local laws, embodying the serious and pragmatic nature of their hold.', 'nord, guard, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath Hold, they grew up surrounded by the region''s unique culture centered around death and burial traditions. After serving in the Imperial Legion during their younger years, they returned home to serve in the local guard force, bringing military discipline and experience to their role protecting the strategically important southern hold.', 'Stoic and dutiful, with a no-nonsense approach to their responsibilities that reflects Falkreath''s somber atmosphere. They maintain a professional demeanor at all times, showing respect for both local traditions and Imperial law, while harboring a deep pride in their hold''s historical significance.', 'Weather-beaten and hardy, with a sturdy Nordic build suited to long hours of patrol in the cold, rainy climate of Falkreath. Their face bears the marks of years of outdoor duty, with alert eyes constantly scanning for threats.', '* Jarl Siddgeir - Direct superior and leader they serve with loyalty * Fellow Guards - Close-knit brotherhood forged through shared duty * Local Citizens - Professional but protective relationship as their defender * Bandits and Criminals - Adversarial relationship as enemies of law and order * Imperial Legion - Maintains positive connections from previous service', 'Serves as a member of Falkreath''s guard force, responsible for maintaining law and order within the hold''s capital and surrounding areas. Their duties include regular patrols, criminal investigation, citizen protection, and defense of the hold''s strategic southern border position.', '* Proficient in both one-handed weapons and archery for versatile combat capability * Trained in standard Imperial military tactics and guard protocols * Experienced in wilderness survival and tracking in Falkreath''s dense forests * Knowledge of local laws and procedures for proper law enforcement * Skilled in basic investigation techniques for solving local crimes', 'Speaks in a gruff, authoritative tone typical of Nord guards, often using common guard phrases and local Falkreath references. Their speech is direct and professional, befitting their role as a representative of hold authority.', '* Maintain peace and order in Falkreath Hold through vigilant service * Protect citizens from increasing bandit activity in the region * Advance within the guard ranks through dedicated service * Uphold the reputation of Falkreath as a secure and well-regulated hold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('haafingar_guard', 'A dedicated law enforcement officer serving in Skyrim''s Haafingar hold, tasked with maintaining order and protecting citizens across the region''s settlements and roadways. As a representative of both Imperial and local authority, they serve as the first line of defense against bandits, wildlife, and other threats while enforcing Hold laws with stern professionalism.', 'nord, guard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Haafingar Hold, they joined the guard force after serving several years in the Imperial Legion during their youth. Their military experience and intimate knowledge of the region made them an ideal candidate for the guard force, where they''ve served with distinction for over a decade protecting settlements like Dragon Bridge and patrolling the roads between farms and outposts.', 'Dutiful and vigilant, with a strong sense of responsibility toward protecting both Imperial and Nordic citizens under their jurisdiction. While generally stern and no-nonsense when performing their duties, they maintain a pragmatic approach to minor infractions and show genuine concern for the wellbeing of law-abiding citizens. Their years of service have instilled a healthy skepticism toward strangers while remaining approachable to those seeking help.', 'A hardy Nord of average height and sturdy build, weathered by years of outdoor patrol duty. Bears several small scars from encounters with wildlife and bandits, with callused hands from weapons training and regular guard duty.', '* Captain Aldis - Direct superior officer who oversees guard training and deployment * Fellow Haafingar Guards - Close-knit brotherhood forged through shared duty * Local Farmers & Merchants - Professional relationships maintained through regular patrols * Bandits & Poachers - Persistent adversaries requiring constant vigilance * Imperial Legion - Maintains cooperative relationship with local garrison', 'Serves as a guard in Haafingar Hold, responsible for maintaining law and order, protecting civilians, and defending against threats to safety and property. Regular duties include patrolling assigned routes, investigating crimes, apprehending criminals, and providing assistance to citizens in need.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with sword and shield techniques * Trained archer capable of defending against both wildlife and hostile humans * Expert knowledge of local geography and common patrol routes * Basic investigation and crime scene assessment abilities * Experienced in crowd control and civilian protection protocols', 'Speaks with clear authority using direct, professional language typical of law enforcement. Frequently employs common guard phrases and local Nordic expressions, delivered with a traditional Haafingar accent.', '* Maintain peace and order throughout Haafingar Hold * Protect citizens from threats both mundane and extraordinary * Advance within the guard ranks through dedicated service * Uphold both Imperial law and Nordic traditions in daily duties');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hjaalmarch_guard', 'A dedicated member of the Hjaalmarch Hold guard force stationed at Stonehills, tasked with protecting the valuable mining operations and local citizens. This steadfast protector represents Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone''s authority in the remote settlement, maintaining vigilance over both the mine''s interests and the safety of its workers.', 'nord, guard, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Hjaalmarch''s harsh marshlands, they joined the guard force after serving in the Imperial Legion during their younger years. Their experience with the Legion''s disciplined structure and combat training made them an ideal candidate for guard duty in the strategically important mining settlement of Stonehills.', 'Stoic and professional, with a strong sense of duty that reflects their military background and current responsibilities. They maintain a vigilant demeanor while showing patience with law-abiding citizens, though they remain constantly alert due to the settlement''s isolated location and vulnerability to bandits or wildlife.', 'Weather-beaten features typical of those who spend their days exposed to Hjaalmarch''s harsh elements, with a sturdy, military bearing from years of guard duty. Their physique is well-maintained through regular patrols and combat readiness training, showing the physical resilience required for their position.', '* Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - Sworn to serve and represent her authority * Stonehills Miners - Professional but cordial relationship with the local workers * Thoring - Occasional visits to Morthal''s Moorside Inn when off-duty * Fellow Hjaalmarch Guards - Strong bonds of camaraderie and mutual support', 'Serves as a guard in Hjaalmarch Hold, specifically stationed at Stonehills to protect the Rockwallow Mine and its workers. Their duties include maintaining security, deterring criminal activity, and ensuring the safe operation of this important mining settlement.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with sword and shield techniques * Trained archer capable of defending against threats at range * Experienced in light armor combat and patrol tactics * Knowledge of local laws and guard procedures * Survival skills suited to Hjaalmarch''s harsh environment', 'Speaks with the formal, authoritative tone expected of a guard, often using standard patrol phrases and official warnings. Their accent reflects their Hjaalmarch origins, while their military background shows in their clear, direct manner of communication.', '* Maintain the security and prosperity of Stonehills and its mining operations * Uphold the law and protect citizens of Hjaalmarch from threats * Advance within the guard ranks through dedicated service * Ensure the continued safe operation of Rockwallow Mine');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imperial_guard', 'A disciplined and stalwart defender of Imperial interests who serves as both military enforcer and civil peacekeeper in Imperial-controlled territories of Skyrim. These guards represent the Empire''s direct authority in the province, maintaining order through regular patrols and law enforcement while standing ready to defend against both common criminals and Stormcloak insurgents.', 'imperial, guard, skyrimall, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Recruited from the local Imperial-aligned population and trained in the rigid traditions of the Imperial Legion. Most guards served in various military campaigns before being assigned to civilian peacekeeping duties, with many having fought in skirmishes against the Stormcloaks. Their extensive training at Imperial garrisons instills both combat prowess and an understanding of Imperial law and procedure.', 'Stern and dutiful, with an unwavering commitment to Imperial law and order. They maintain a professional demeanor at all times, showing respect to law-abiding citizens while remaining vigilant for any signs of criminal activity or Stormcloak sympathy. Their military background manifests in a direct, no-nonsense approach to their duties.', 'Well-built and physically fit from regular training and patrol duties, with the straight-backed posture typical of military training. Most are Imperials or Nords, ranging from their mid-twenties to late forties, maintaining the physical standards required for guard duty. Their faces often show the weathering of regular outdoor patrol duty in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Imperial Legion - Strong loyalty and operational subordination to Legion command * Local Jarls - Professional working relationship in Imperial-held holds * Fellow Guards - Close brotherhood forged through shared duty and training * Local Citizens - Professional protector relationship with law-abiding residents * Stormcloak Sympathizers - Tense adversarial relationship requiring constant vigilance', 'Serves as both military presence and civil law enforcement in Imperial-controlled holds. Duties include regular patrols, criminal investigation, tax collection, and maintaining public order. They also serve as the first line of defense against any military threats to their assigned hold.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat, particularly with Imperial swords * Skilled archer capable of both battlefield and precision shooting * Trained in light and heavy armor combat techniques * Expert in local law enforcement and criminal investigation * Competent in crowd control and civil peacekeeping operations', 'Formal and authoritative, employing military terminology and Imperial legal phrases. Their speech reflects their training with frequent use of set phrases like "Stop right there', 'back off!"""');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ivarstead_guard', 'A dedicated member of the Rift''s guard force stationed in the quiet town of Ivarstead, serving as both protector and representative of Stormcloak authority. This guard maintains vigilant watch over both local matters and pilgrims heading to High Hrothgar, while dealing with the unique challenges of a town situated at the foot of the Seven Thousand Steps.', 'nord, guard, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in the Rift, this guard served initially as part of Riften''s city watch before being assigned to the more peaceful but strategically important post in Ivarstead. Having witnessed the rise of the Stormcloak rebellion, they chose to maintain their position serving the Hold even as political tensions rose across Skyrim, believing in the importance of protecting common folk regardless of the larger conflict.', 'Stoic and professional, maintaining a formal demeanor that reflects their position of authority while showing appropriate respect to pilgrims and travelers. Though generally serious about their duties, they harbor a deep appreciation for Ivarstead''s peaceful nature and take pride in protecting this gateway to High Hrothgar.', 'A Nord of typical warrior build, weathered by constant outdoor patrols in the harsh climate of the Rift. Shows the physical conditioning required of guard duty, with callused hands from weapons training and a steady, watchful gaze developed through years of service.', '* Fellow Guards - Close working relationship with other patrol members * Wilhelm - Professional relationship with the innkeeper regarding traveler activity * Klimmek - Respectful association with the regular pilgrim supplier * Gwilin - Keeps watch over the wood elf''s safety during lumber work * Temba Wide-Arm - Maintains awareness of her bear problems to ensure town safety', 'Serves as one of four guards stationed in Ivarstead, responsible for maintaining law and order while protecting both locals and pilgrims. Patrols assigned sectors of the town, from the bridge to Shroud Hearth Barrow or from Fellstar Farm to the Seven Thousand Steps, depending on rotation.', '* Proficient in both one-handed weapons and archery for varied combat situations * Trained in standard guard procedures and patrol techniques * Experienced in wilderness survival and mountain navigation * Knowledgeable about local laws and customs of the Rift * Basic investigation skills for handling local disturbances', 'Speaks in the characteristic guard manner - formal, authoritative, and often stern, with typical Nordic accent. Frequently uses standard guard phrases and warnings while maintaining professional distance in conversations.', '* Maintain the peace and security of Ivarstead and its people * Protect pilgrims making their way to High Hrothgar * Uphold Stormcloak authority in the region while ensuring citizen safety * Keep Shroud Hearth Barrow secure from troublemakers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('markarth_city_guard', 'A stern and vigilant member of Markarth''s city guard force who maintains order through a complex system of corruption and unofficial agreements. Operating under the surface tension between the Silver-Blood family, the Forsworn, and the Jarl''s authority, these guards embody the city''s darker nature while maintaining its facade of order.', 'nord, guard, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, most Markarth guards come from local Nordic families who have lived under the shadow of the Forsworn conflict for generations. They''ve witnessed the city''s transformation from a site of violent uprising to its current state of tense stability, leading them to value pragmatic control over justice.', 'Cynical and intimidating, characterized by a strong desire to maintain the status quo through any means necessary. They exhibit a dismissive attitude toward outsiders and newcomers, actively discouraging investigation into the city''s affairs while showing calculated loyalty to those who maintain Markarth''s power structure.', 'Typically Nord males of sturdy build, weathered by constant patrols in the harsh mountain climate of the Reach. Their faces often bear scars from encounters with Forsworn raiders, and their physical bearing reflects years of guard duty in the stone city''s steep streets.', '* Jarl Igmund - Official superior and leader of Markarth * Thonar Silver-Blood - Secret paymaster who maintains corruption * Madanach - Complicated arrangement through Silver-Blood family * Fellow Guards - Strong brotherhood built on shared secrets * General Population - Maintaining authoritative distance', 'Serves as both military defender and civil law enforcement in Markarth, operating under the official authority of the Jarl. Their duties include protecting the city from external threats, maintaining internal order, and preserving the delicate power balance between various factions through both official and unofficial means.', '* Trained in standard guard combat techniques with sword and shield * Proficient in local law enforcement and crowd control * Experienced in urban warfare and city defense * Knowledge of Markarth''s complex political landscape * Skilled in intimidation and maintaining public order', 'Uses terse, authoritative language with a threatening undertone, often delivering warnings and advice in the form of barely veiled threats. Their speech patterns emphasize keeping order and discouraging outsider involvement in city affairs.', '* Maintain the status quo and existing power structure in Markarth * Preserve the profitable arrangement between the Silver-Bloods and the Forsworn * Ensure personal survival and prosperity through strategic loyalty * Keep outsiders from disrupting the city''s delicate balance of power');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('morthal_guard', 'A dedicated member of Morthal''s guard force who serves as both protector and peacekeeper in the misty, mysterious hold capital. Though many outsiders view Morthal as a backwater, this guard takes immense pride in defending their post at one of Skyrim''s most enigmatic settlements, serving loyally under the prophetic Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone.', 'nord, guard, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Hjaalmarch, they grew up witnessing the unique challenges of protecting a hold dominated by treacherous marshlands and ancient Nordic ruins. After years of training and proving their worth through patrols of the dangerous swamps, they earned their position as a full-fledged guard in Morthal''s small but dedicated security force.', 'Stoic and vigilant, with a deep-seated sense of duty to both Morthal and its eccentric inhabitants. While maintaining professional authority, they show particular patience and understanding toward the town''s unique character, including Jarl Idgrod''s prophetic visions and the general supernatural atmosphere that pervades the settlement.', 'Weather-beaten and hardy, with a sturdy Nordic build suited to long hours of patrol in harsh conditions. Their face bears the marks of exposure to Hjaalmarch''s harsh elements, with calculating eyes constantly scanning for threats in the mists.', '* Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - Respected leader whose mystical insights they''ve learned to trust * Aslfur - The Jarl''s husband and steward, who handles their pay and duty assignments * Fellow Guards - Close-knit brotherhood forged by shared duties in dangerous territory * Morthal Citizens - Protective relationship with locals, especially during vampire investigations * Benor - Friendly rival and fellow warrior who helps maintain town security', 'Serves as a guard in Morthal''s security force, responsible for protecting the town from both mundane and supernatural threats. Duties include regular patrols, criminal investigation, citizen protection, and occasional swamp expeditions to clear out dangerous wildlife or bandits.', '* Proficient with sword and bow, specialized in marsh terrain combat * Experienced in tracking through swampland and detecting signs of supernatural activity * Knowledge of local laws and procedures for maintaining order * Basic understanding of vampire and witch lore, necessary for Morthal''s unique threats * Skilled in cold weather survival and navigation through misty conditions', 'Speaks with a strong Nordic accent and authoritative tone, though tempered with the wisdom of one who has seen Morthal''s stranger side. Uses direct, no-nonsense language while maintaining professional courtesy.', '* Maintain the safety and security of Morthal against both natural and supernatural threats * Earn promotion to guard captain or higher rank within Hjaalmarch''s security force * Preserve Morthal''s unique character while protecting it from those who would do it harm * Master the challenging art of patrolling and protecting in marsh environments');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('pale_hold_guard', 'A dedicated law enforcement officer patrolling the harsh roads of The Pale, representing the authority of Jarl Skald the Elder. This vigilant guard takes his duties seriously, maintaining order along the treacherous northern routes while showing particular attention to the area around Loreius Farm.', 'nord, guard, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in The Pale, this Nord guard worked his way up through the hold''s military ranks during the Civil War period. After proving himself capable in several skirmishes with bandits and surviving the harsh northern climate, he was assigned to patrol one of the hold''s vital trade routes, gaining intimate knowledge of the local area and its residents.', 'Stern, dutiful, and no-nonsense in his approach to law enforcement, demonstrating unwavering dedication to maintaining order in his jurisdiction. Shows impatience with time-wasters but maintains professional courtesy, while harboring a deep-seated suspicion of unusual travelers and potential troublemakers that frequent the roads.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with weather-beaten features hardened by constant exposure to The Pale''s harsh climate. Bears several small scars from past confrontations with bandits and wildlife, with a particularly noticeable one across his left cheek.', '* Jarl Skald the Elder - Direct superior and leader of The Pale * Vantus Loreius - Local farmer under his jurisdiction whom he regularly checks on * Fellow Pale Hold Guards - Maintains professional camaraderie with other patrolling guards * Cicero - Subject of investigation following civilian complaints * Local merchants and travelers - Professional relationship as protector of the roads', 'Serves as a dedicated hold guard for The Pale, responsible for patrolling the road near Loreius Farm and maintaining law and order in the surrounding area. Primary duties include investigating reported crimes, protecting travelers, and ensuring the safety of local residents.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat and shield tactics * Skilled archer capable of defending against bandits and wildlife * Experienced in patrol techniques and criminal investigation * Knowledgeable about local laws and regulations * Resistant to cold weather and harsh conditions typical of The Pale', 'Speaks in short, direct sentences with a commanding tone typical of Nord law enforcement. Uses formal, authoritative language when addressing civilians, often with an undertone of impatience.', '* Maintain law and order along his assigned patrol route * Protect the citizens and travelers of The Pale from criminal elements * Advance within the ranks of the hold guard through dedicated service * Preserve the peace during the ongoing civil war while remaining loyal to the hold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reach_hold_guard', 'A dedicated guard of the Reach who maintains vigilant watch over Left Hand Mine, representing the authority of Jarl Igmund and the city of Markarth. Though seemingly a typical guard, they play a crucial role in protecting both the valuable mining operations and the miners who work there from the ever-present threats of Forsworn raids and bandit attacks.', 'nord, guard, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, they grew up witnessing the constant struggles between the Nords and the Forsworn, which shaped their dedication to maintaining order. After serving in Markarth''s city watch, they were assigned to the strategically important Left Hand Mine post, where they''ve served faithfully for several years, earning respect from both the miners and their superiors for their reliable service.', 'Disciplined and vigilant, with a strong sense of duty that drives them to maintain their post regardless of weather or danger. Shows practical wisdom in knowing when to exercise authority strictly and when to be more lenient with minor infractions, particularly with the hardworking miners they protect.', 'A hardy Nord of average height and sturdy build, weathered by constant exposure to the harsh elements of the Reach. Bears several small scars from previous encounters with Forsworn raiders, and maintains the straight-backed posture typical of long-serving guards.', '* Jarl Igmund - Sworn to serve and protect his interests * Left Hand Mine Workers - Protective relationship as their guardian * Fellow Reach Guards - Strong bonds of brotherhood and mutual support * Forsworn - Viewed as dangerous enemies to be vigilantly watched for * Miners - Professional but friendly relationship built on mutual respect', 'Serves as a dedicated guard at Left Hand Mine, responsible for protecting both the valuable mining operations and the miners who work there. Their duties include maintaining security, checking for suspicious activities, and serving as the first line of defense against potential Forsworn attacks.', '* Proficient with sword and shield in the Imperial fighting style * Skilled archer capable of defending against long-range threats * Basic knowledge of local laws and procedures * Experienced in identifying potential Forsworn activity * Weather-hardened and capable of maintaining long watches in harsh conditions', 'Speaks in the authoritative yet approachable manner typical of Reach guards, often using common guard phrases and maintaining a formal tone. Their accent carries the distinct inflections of the Reach, mixing Nordic and local influences.', '* Maintain the safety and security of Left Hand Mine and its workers * Advance within the ranks of the Reach Guard through dedicated service * Protect the Reach from Forsworn insurgents and other threats * Earn enough to eventually retire with honor in Markarth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rift_guard', 'A member of the Rift Guard serving in Riften and the surrounding hold, balancing official law enforcement duties with the reality of the city''s corrupt underbelly. This guard maintains an outward appearance of authority while participating in the complex web of bribes and favors that characterizes Riften''s power structure under Maven Black-Briar''s influence.', 'nord, guard, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in the Rift, this guard grew up witnessing the delicate balance between legitimate commerce and criminal enterprise that defines Riften. After serving in the civil war, they joined the Rift Guard, quickly learning that survival in Riften meant knowing when to enforce the law and when to look the other way.', 'Pragmatic and world-weary, the Rift Guard maintains a professional demeanor while harboring a cynical outlook on justice in Riften. They are willing to accept bribes and ignore certain criminal activities, not out of greed but from a practical understanding of how power truly flows in the city. Despite this compromise, they remain committed to protecting citizens from genuine threats.', 'A Nordic guard of average height and sturdy build, weathered by years of patrol duty in the Rift''s harsh climate. Bears several small scars from encounters with wildlife and bandits, with callused hands from years of wielding weapons and maintaining order.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Influential employer through proxy of the Jarl position, demanding absolute loyalty * Thieves Guild - Complicated professional relationship involving bribes and selective enforcement * Local Merchants - Mixed relations ranging from protection arrangements to subtle extortion * Fellow Guards - Strong bonds of camaraderie tempered by shared understanding of Riften''s corruption * Local Citizens - Generally respectful but distant relationship maintained through regular patrols', 'Serves as a member of the Rift Guard, responsible for maintaining order in Riften and the surrounding hold. Duties include regular patrols, investigating crimes, protecting citizens and property, and maintaining Maven Black-Briar''s preferred status quo.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons and shield combat techniques * Trained in basic investigation and peacekeeping procedures * Experienced in crowd control and civil dispute resolution * Knowledgeable about local laws and their selective enforcement * Skilled at detecting lies and assessing threats', 'Speaks with an authoritative Nordic accent, employing formal guard phraseology mixed with local Riften colloquialisms. Often uses stern warnings and official-sounding threats while being careful to maintain plausible deniability regarding corruption.', '* Maintain position and income through careful balance of official duties and unofficial arrangements * Protect citizens from serious crimes while navigating Riften''s complex power structure * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually retire comfortably * Avoid drawing unwanted attention from either Maven Black-Briar or the Thieves Guild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('riften_guard', 'A member of Riften''s guard force who walks the line between upholding the law and turning a blind eye to certain criminal activities, particularly those involving the influential Thieves Guild. Despite their sometimes questionable ethics, they maintain order in one of Skyrim''s most corrupt cities while serving under Jarl Laila Law-Giver.', 'nord, guard, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in the Rift, they joined the guard force after witnessing the rising crime and corruption in their home city. Their position has led them to develop a pragmatic approach to law enforcement, understanding that in Riften, absolute adherence to the law is often impossible and sometimes counterproductive. Years of service have taught them which crimes to pursue and which to overlook for the sake of maintaining a delicate balance in the city.', 'Cynical and world-weary, yet maintains a strong sense of duty to protect Riften''s common citizens. Shows flexibility in interpreting laws, often accepting bribes or turning a blind eye to certain criminal activities while cracking down hard on truly destructive behavior. Maintains a professional demeanor in public but harbors a deep understanding of Riften''s complex power dynamics.', 'Weather-beaten Nordic features with numerous small scars from years of guard duty. Muscular build maintained through regular patrol duties and combat training. Generally stands with perfect posture to project authority, though often adopts a more relaxed stance when dealing with known local figures.', '* Jarl Laila Law-Giver - Direct superior, though relationship is mostly ceremonial * Maven Black-Briar - Unofficial authority figure whose influence cannot be ignored * Thieves Guild - Complex relationship involving selective enforcement and occasional cooperation * Fellow Guards - Strong bonds of brotherhood despite knowing some are corrupt * City Watch Captain - Direct supervisor who understands the need for pragmatic law enforcement', 'Serves as a member of Riften''s guard force, responsible for maintaining order, protecting citizens, and enforcing laws within the city limits. Patrols assigned sectors of the city, responds to criminal activity, and manages the collection of bounties and fines. Also assists in the defense of the city during external threats.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons and shield combat techniques * Trained in standard guard procedures and city law enforcement protocols * Experienced in handling civil disputes and maintaining public order * Skilled at detecting suspicious behavior and common criminal tactics * Basic knowledge of local criminal organizations and their operations', 'Speaks with a firm, authoritative tone typical of Riften guards, often employing local idioms and guard jargon. Uses formal language when executing official duties but can shift to a more casual tone when dealing with familiar citizens or fellow guards.', '* Maintain personal safety and financial security through balanced enforcement of laws * Protect Riften''s citizens while navigating the city''s complex power structure * Build a retirement fund through both legitimate and questionable means * Advance within the guard ranks without compromising too many principles');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('roadside_guard', 'A disciplined Imperial soldier assigned to patrol duty near Loreius Farm after the Pale falls under Legion control. As a front-line representative of Imperial authority in a formerly Stormcloak hold, he maintains strict vigilance and enforces the law with unwavering dedication.', 'imperial, guard, pale, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, he joined the Imperial Legion seeking structure and purpose during the tumultuous years leading up to the Civil War. After proving himself in several skirmishes, he was assigned to the Pale as part of the occupation force, tasked with maintaining order and representing Imperial authority in newly conquered territory.', 'Stern and dutiful, he approaches his responsibilities with rigid professionalism and little patience for idle conversation. Despite his gruff exterior, he takes his role as protector of civilian travelers seriously and maintains a keen eye for suspicious activity along his patrol route.', 'A weathered Imperial man in his mid-thirties with a sturdy, athletic build shaped by years of military service. His face bears the subtle scars of combat experience, and his posture reflects years of military discipline and training.', '* Imperial Legion - Sworn member and loyal soldier * Loreius Farm residents - Maintains professional oversight of their safety * Local travelers - Provides protection and law enforcement * Former Stormcloak sympathizers - Tense but professional interactions', 'Serves as an Imperial Legion guard stationed along the road near Loreius Farm, responsible for maintaining order and enforcing Imperial law in formerly Stormcloak territory. His duties include patrolling the road, protecting travelers, and apprehending criminals with bounties in the Pale.', '* Trained in Imperial Legion combat tactics and patrol procedures * Proficient with sword and bow for both close and ranged combat * Experienced in law enforcement and criminal apprehension * Skilled in maintaining order in hostile territory', 'Speaks in clipped, authoritative tones with the formal manner typical of Imperial Legion soldiers. His responses are brief and direct, reflecting his military training and no-nonsense approach to duty.', '* Maintain Imperial control and order in his assigned territory * Prevent any resurgence of Stormcloak influence in the region * Earn recognition for exemplary service to potentially advance within Legion ranks');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('shor''s_stone_guard', 'A dedicated guardian of Shor''s Stone who maintains vigilant watch over this strategic mining settlement in the Rift. As part of Maven Black-Briar''s security forces, they represent both local law enforcement and a crucial defensive position against potential threats from nearby Fort Greenwall.', 'nord, guard, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in the Rift, they began their career as a guard in Riften before being assigned to the more demanding post at Shor''s Stone due to their exceptional dedication and combat prowess. The strategic importance of protecting the settlement''s valuable iron mine and watching over Fort Greenwall has shaped their serious approach to duty and heightened sense of vigilance.', 'Stern and dutiful, with an unwavering commitment to protecting both Shor''s Stone''s residents and its valuable mining operations. Shows particular concern for the mine''s safety and maintains a cautious attitude toward strangers, though remains professional and approachable to law-abiding citizens.', 'Sturdy Nord of average height with a muscular build developed through years of guard duty and combat training. Weather-beaten features from constant outdoor patrols reflect their years of service, with numerous small scars from past confrontations with bandits and wildlife.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Serves under her authority as Jarl of the Rift * Filnjar - Works closely with the settlement''s blacksmith to maintain order * Fellow Guards - Strong bonds with other Shor''s Stone guards through shared duty * Sylgja - Protects the local miner and ensures her safety * Odfel - Watches over the mine worker''s wellbeing * Stormcloak Soldiers - Maintains alliance and coordinates defense strategies', 'Serves as one of three dedicated guards protecting the strategic mining settlement of Shor''s Stone. Responsibilities include patrolling designated routes, monitoring mine security, maintaining law and order, and coordinating with other guards to ensure comprehensive settlement protection.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with sword and shield techniques * Skilled archer capable of defensive and offensive bow combat * Expert in guard patrol tactics and settlement defense strategies * Trained in criminal detection and law enforcement procedures * Experienced in wilderness survival and tracking', 'Speaks with a deep, authoritative Nordic accent typical of Rift guards, employing formal and direct language that emphasizes law enforcement and security. Frequently uses cautionary phrases and stern warnings while maintaining professional courtesy.', '* Maintain the security and prosperity of Shor''s Stone against all threats * Protect the strategic value of Redbelly Mine for the Rift''s economy * Advance within the Rift''s guard hierarchy through dedicated service * Monitor Fort Greenwall for potential military developments');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('silver-blood_guard', 'A hardened mercenary employed by Markarth''s influential Silver-Blood family to maintain order in the notorious Cidhna Mine prison. These guards represent the iron fist of Silver-Blood authority, combining the brutal efficiency of professional soldiers with the unwavering loyalty of well-paid enforcers.', 'nord, guard, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Most Silver-Blood Guards are former soldiers or mercenaries who proved their worth through violence and unwavering loyalty. Many fought in the Forsworn Uprising or served in various mercenary companies before finding steady employment with the Silver-Blood family, who valued their combination of combat experience and moral flexibility.', 'Cruel and uncompromising, Silver-Blood Guards take pride in their authority and show little sympathy for prisoners. They maintain a professional demeanor when dealing with citizens but relish the opportunity to exercise power over inmates, often using excessive force to maintain order. Their loyalty to the Silver-Blood family is absolute, bought with generous pay and the promise of protection.', 'Typically Nordic or Imperial in ancestry, these guards are physically imposing with battle-hardened bodies shaped by years of combat. Most bear various scars from their mercenary days, and their faces often show weather-beaten features and stern expressions that reflect their harsh profession.', '* Silver-Blood Family - Primary employers who provide generous compensation for loyalty * Thonar Silver-Blood - Direct superior who issues orders and oversees operations * Markarth City Guard - Maintain professional but sometimes tense relationship due to overlapping jurisdictions * Prisoners - Antagonistic relationship marked by contempt and harsh treatment * Fellow Silver-Blood Guards - Strong camaraderie built on shared duties and experiences', 'Serves as a private security force for the Silver-Blood family, primarily tasked with guarding Cidhna Mine and its prisoners. Their duties include maintaining order, preventing escapes, overseeing prisoner labor, and protecting Silver-Blood interests within the mine.', '* Proficient in close-quarters combat, particularly with maces and short blades * Experienced in crowd control and prisoner management techniques * Skilled in intimidation and psychological manipulation * Basic archery abilities for long-range threat management * Trained in riot control and group combat tactics', 'Speaks in short, threatening commands with a gruff, authoritative tone that brooks no argument. Their vocabulary is simple but effective, often peppered with threats and reminders of their authority.', '* Maintain position of authority and continue earning substantial pay from the Silver-Bloods * Keep order in Cidhna Mine through whatever means necessary * Advance within the Silver-Blood organization''s hierarchy * Prevent any prisoner escapes or uprisings that could damage their reputation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('solitude_guard', 'A dedicated member of Solitude''s city guard force who serves as both local law enforcement and an auxiliary of the Imperial Legion. They represent the military might and civil authority of both Solitude and the Empire, trained to maintain order in one of Skyrim''s most important cities while also standing ready to defend against both external threats and internal dissent.', 'nord, guard, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Haafingar Hold, they enlisted in the city guard force after showing promise during basic Imperial Legion training under Captain Aldis. Having witnessed the death of High King Torygg, they developed an unwavering loyalty to Jarl Elisif and the Imperial cause, viewing their role as crucial in maintaining stability during these turbulent times.', 'Disciplined and professional, with a strong sense of duty to both Solitude and the Empire. They maintain a formal demeanor while interacting with citizens and take pride in upholding the law, though they can be stern and uncompromising when confronting criminals. Despite their serious nature, they share a camaraderie with fellow guards and take pride in Solitude''s status as Skyrim''s capital.', 'Athletic and well-built from regular training and patrol duties, with a sturdy Nordic frame typical of Skyrim''s warriors. Their posture is straight and military-precise, reflecting their professional training and discipline. Weather-worn features show the marks of countless hours spent patrolling Solitude''s streets and walls.', '* Captain Aldis - Commanding officer and mentor in combat training * Jarl Elisif - Sworn to protect and serve, with particular loyalty following High King Torygg''s death * Fellow Guards - Close-knit brotherhood forged through shared duties and dangers * General Tullius - Ultimate superior officer through Imperial chain of command * Stormcloak Sympathizers - Viewed with suspicion as potential threats to city security', 'Serves as both a city guard and auxiliary member of the Imperial Legion, responsible for maintaining law and order within Solitude while also standing ready for military action. Their duties include regular patrols, criminal investigation, crowd control during executions, and training exercises in Castle Dour''s courtyard.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with sword and shield techniques * Trained archer capable of both city defense and criminal pursuit * Expert in local law enforcement and criminal investigation procedures * Basic knowledge of Imperial military tactics and formations * Skilled in crowd control and civil peacekeeping operations', 'Formal and professional, consistently using respectful terms like ''sir'' regardless of the addressee''s gender. Their speech reflects military training with clear, direct statements and a tone of authority.', '* Maintain peace and order in Solitude while supporting the Imperial cause * Advance within the ranks of the city guard through dedicated service * Protect Jarl Elisif and ensure Solitude remains the capital of Skyrim * Help defeat the Stormcloak rebellion and restore full Imperial control');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stormcloak_guard', 'A dedicated member of the Stormcloak military force serving as both soldier and law enforcer in holds controlled by Ulfric''s rebellion. These hardy Nordic warriors represent the front line of the Stormcloak cause, maintaining order while embodying the ideals of Nordic independence and traditional values.', 'nord, guard, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, likely from a traditional Nordic family that has long resented Imperial influence. Joined the Stormcloak rebellion after the Markarth Incident and the outlawing of Talos worship, having either served previously in the local hold guard or coming from a farming/hunting background that provided crucial survival and combat skills.', 'Fiercely patriotic and devoted to the Stormcloak cause, with a strong sense of Nordic pride and tradition. Generally suspicious of outsiders and non-Nords, but maintains professional conduct in their duties. Shows unwavering loyalty to Ulfric Stormcloak and believes firmly in Skyrim''s right to independence, often expressing these views openly.', 'Typically a robust Nord of athletic build, weathered by Skyrim''s harsh climate and regular combat training. Bears the characteristic Nordic features including fair skin and strong bone structure, with various battle scars marking their experience in combat.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Revered leader and inspiration for their service * Fellow Stormcloak Soldiers - Brothers and sisters in arms * Imperial Legion - Sworn enemies representing foreign oppression * Local Hold Citizens - Subjects under their protection * Thalmor - Despised enemies seen as the true threat to Skyrim', 'Serves as both military soldier and civil law enforcement in Stormcloak-controlled holds. Responsible for maintaining order, protecting citizens, investigating crimes, and defending the hold from various threats including Imperial forces, bandits, and dangerous wildlife.', '* Proficient in both one-handed and two-handed weapon combat * Skilled archer capable of both defensive and offensive bow tactics * Expert in shield techniques and defensive maneuvers * Trained in both light and heavy armor usage * Experienced in local law enforcement and criminal investigation * Knowledgeable in Nordic customs and traditional combat techniques', 'Speaks with a strong Nordic accent, using direct and often stern language filled with references to Skyrim''s independence and Stormcloak victory. Frequently employs traditional Nordic phrases and shows particular contempt when discussing the Empire or Thalmor.', '* Secure complete independence for Skyrim under Stormcloak leadership * Maintain law and order in their assigned hold while upholding Nordic traditions * Drive out Imperial influence from Skyrim * Restore the worship of Talos to its rightful place in Nordic society * Protect and serve the local population while advancing the Stormcloak cause');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('whiterun_guard', 'A dedicated member of Whiterun''s city guard force who serves as both protector and law enforcer within the hold''s capital. Like their fellow guards, they are known for their vigilant nature and unwavering loyalty to Jarl Balgruuf, as well as their infamous tendency to reminisce about their pre-arrow-to-the-knee adventuring days.', 'nord, guard, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun Hold, they spent their youth training in combat and learning the ways of Nordic warfare. Before joining the guard, they lived as an adventurer until an injury (the famous arrow to the knee) led them to seek a more stable profession protecting their home city. Their years of experience have made them intimately familiar with every corner of Whiterun and its inhabitants.', 'Dutiful and alert, with a strong sense of justice tempered by practical wisdom gained from years of service. They maintain a somewhat world-weary but humorous outlook, often making dry observations about sweetroll theft and the dangers of Shouting. Despite their sometimes cynical demeanor, they take their responsibilities seriously and show genuine concern for the citizens under their protection.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with a muscular build maintained through regular patrol duties and combat training. Weather-beaten features and cautious eyes reflect years of outdoor guard duty. Bears some old battle scars, including the famous knee injury that ended their adventuring career.', '* Jarl Balgruuf - Sworn to serve and protect * Commander Caius - Direct superior officer * Irileth - Housecarl to the Jarl and guard supervisor * Fellow Guards - Strong bonds of brotherhood and shared duty * Citizens of Whiterun - Protective relationship as their guardian', 'Serves as a member of the Whiterun Guard, responsible for maintaining law and order within the city walls and surrounding hold. Duties include regular patrols, criminal investigation, city defense, and occasional dragon threat response. They rotate between guard posts, including gates, marketplace, and residential districts.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with sword and shield * Skilled archer capable of defending city walls * Trained in heavy armor combat techniques * Basic knowledge of local laws and criminal investigation * Experienced in crowd control and peacekeeping', 'Speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a thick Nordic accent, often punctuated by well-known guard phrases and local colloquialisms. Frequently makes references to their past adventuring life and the infamous arrow to the knee.', '* Maintain peace and order in Whiterun * Protect citizens from threats both internal and external * Advance within the guard ranks * Preserve neutrality in the civil war while defending Whiterun''s interests * Eventually retire with honor and a full pension');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('windhelm_guard', 'A disciplined member of Windhelm''s guard force who serves as both protector and enforcer of the city''s laws under Jarl Ulfric Stormcloak. Like most Windhelm guards, they embody the harsh resilience of their city while maintaining order in one of Skyrim''s most politically charged environments.', 'nord, guard, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Eastmarch, they grew up witnessing the growing tensions between Nords and other races in Windhelm. After showing promise in combat training and demonstrating unwavering loyalty to Nordic traditions, they were recruited into the city guard, serving through both peaceful times and the civil war period.', 'Stern and dutiful, with a strong sense of tradition and loyalty to both Windhelm and Ulfric Stormcloak. While generally fair in enforcing the law, they share some of the city''s inherent prejudices against outsiders and non-Nords, though they maintain professional conduct in their duties.', 'A hardy Nord with weather-worn features, standing slightly above average height with a sturdy, muscular build developed through years of guard duty in harsh conditions. Bears minor scars from past confrontations with criminals and wildlife, typical for a guard serving in one of Skyrim''s most dangerous holds.', '* Jarl Ulfric Stormcloak - Direct superior and object of loyal service * Fellow Windhelm Guards - Close-knit brotherhood forged through shared duty * Captain of the Guard - Immediate superior officer * Local Nord Citizens - Protective relationship as their guardian * Dark Elf Residents - Tense but professional relationship as peacekeeper', 'Serves as a member of Windhelm''s guard force, responsible for maintaining law and order within the city walls and immediate surroundings. Duties include regular patrols, criminal investigation, protection of citizens and property, and defense of the city during emergencies.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons and shield combat techniques * Trained in basic investigation and peacekeeping procedures * Experienced in cold weather survival and patrol techniques * Knowledge of local laws and Guard protocols * Capable of basic first response medical aid', 'Speaks with a thick Nordic accent and uses formal, authoritative language befitting their position. Often employs common guard phrases and local colloquialisms, frequently mentioning their ''sworn duty to protect'' and making references to taking ''arrows in the knee.''', '* Maintain law and order in Windhelm while serving Jarl Ulfric faithfully * Advance within the guard ranks through dedicated service * Protect Nordic traditions and way of life in Windhelm * Keep the peace between the city''s various racial communities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('winterhold_guard', 'A steadfast protector of Winterhold who maintains order in what remains of the once-great city after the Great Collapse. Despite serving in one of Skyrim''s most desolate holds, they maintain unwavering dedication to their duty, representing both the authority of Jarl Korir and the resilient spirit of Winterhold itself.', 'nord, guard, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Winterhold before its devastating collapse, they witnessed their home''s transformation from a prosperous city to a shadow of its former glory. Having lost family members in the Great Collapse, they chose to become a guard to prevent further tragedy and maintain what remains of Winterhold''s dignity. Their deep connection to the city drives their particular disdain for the College of Winterhold, which many locals blame for the catastrophe.', 'Stoic and dutiful, they maintain a professional demeanor despite the harsh conditions and relative isolation of their post. Shows particular vigilance toward the College of Winterhold, harboring the typical local suspicion of mages while maintaining required professional courtesy. Despite the challenges of their position, they take pride in their role as one of Winterhold''s few remaining protectors.', 'Nordic features weathered by constant exposure to the harsh climate of northern Skyrim. Tall and robust build typical of Nord warriors, with numerous small scars from years of service. Their face shows signs of regular exposure to bitter cold and fierce winds.', '* Jarl Korir - Direct superior and leader they serve with unwavering loyalty * Fellow Winterhold Guards - Close-knit brotherhood forged by shared duty in harsh conditions * College of Winterhold - Professional but tense relationship, maintaining necessary security cooperation * Winterhold Citizens - Protective and familiar relationship with the few remaining townspeople * Birna - Frequent interaction as one of the few remaining merchants', 'Serves as a member of Winterhold''s guard force, responsible for maintaining law and order in the hold capital and surrounding areas. Duties include patrolling the treacherous streets, protecting citizens from magical accidents and wildlife, and monitoring College visitors.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons and shield combat techniques * Experienced in cold weather survival and navigation * Basic knowledge of magic recognition for identifying potential threats * Skilled in criminal investigation and peacekeeping procedures * Expert in local geography and hazard awareness', 'Speaks with the characteristic Nordic accent common to Skyrim''s guards, using formal and authoritative tones when addressing citizens and travelers. Frequently references the harsh conditions of Winterhold and maintains professional decorum even in casual conversation.', '* Maintain order and security in Winterhold despite limited resources * Protect citizens from both mundane threats and magical accidents * Preserve what remains of Winterhold''s dignity and authority * Prevent any further catastrophes like the Great Collapse');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('holgeir', 'Holgeir was a formidable Nord warlord whose legendary romance with the huntress Fjori brought peace between warring forest clans in ancient Skyrim. His tragic tale of love, sacrifice, and eventual undeath as a draugr exemplifies the Nordic warrior spirit and deep devotion that transcended even death itself.', 'nord, warrior, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Rising to prominence as a warlord among the forest clans of Skyrim, Holgeir''s life changed dramatically when he met Fjori in battle, where their mutual skill and warrior spirit led to love rather than death. Their union ushered in an era of peace until tragedy struck with a venomous snake bite, leading to a chain of events that ended with both lovers taking their own lives to be reunited in Sovngarde, only to be later raised as draugr by the grieving conjurer Lu''ah Al-Skaven.', 'Holgeir embodies the noble warrior spirit of the Nords, combining martial prowess with a capacity for deep loyalty and sacrifice. His actions reveal both a fierce warrior''s heart and a romantic soul willing to die for love, suggesting a complex character who valued honor, love, and duty above all else. Despite his status as a warlord, he showed wisdom in embracing peace through his union with Fjori.', 'As a Nord warlord, Holgeir would have possessed the typical robust, tall build characteristic of his race, with well-developed musculature from years of combat training and battlefield experience. His ghost form suggests he was likely fair-skinned with the strong features common to Nord warriors, bearing the scars and weathered appearance of a seasoned fighter.', '* Fjori - His beloved wife and equal in combat, whose love brought peace to warring clans * Forest Clans - Former enemies turned peaceful allies following his union with Fjori * Lu''ah Al-Skaven - The conjurer who cursed him and Fjori to undeath as draugr * Local Nords - Likely held him and Fjori in high regard as legendary figures', 'Holgeir served as a warlord of one of the forest clans, leading his people in battle and likely managing territories under his control. After his union with Fjori, he presumably took on a more diplomatic role in maintaining peace between the formerly warring clans.', '* Master warrior skilled in Nordic combat techniques, particularly with axes and shields * Tactical military leadership as demonstrated by his position as warlord * Diplomatic abilities shown through his role in maintaining peace between clans * Likely proficient in traditional Nord hunting and survival skills', 'Holgeir speaks with the formal, poetic cadence common to ancient Nordic warriors, expressing himself with dignity and emotional depth. His few recorded words reveal both nobility and deep affection, particularly in his interactions with Fjori.', '* To be reunited with his beloved Fjori in eternal peace * To break free from the curse of undeath placed upon them * To serve as an inspiration for future generations of Nords through his tale of love and sacrifice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('horgeir', 'Horgeir is a hardworking Nord lumberjack who owns and operates the Dragon Bridge lumber mill, embodying the traditional Nordic values of hard work and hearty drinking. Despite his successful business and generally cheerful demeanor, he struggles with an unhappy marriage and finds solace in his work and evening visits to the local inn.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born and raised in Dragon Bridge, Horgeir built his lumber mill from the ground up, though it once suffered a devastating fire that required rebuilding. His business has thrived during the civil war due to increased demand for lumber, and he has maintained the mill as a crucial part of Dragon Bridge''s economy, serving both Imperial and Stormcloak forces alike.', 'Horgeir is a jovial and outgoing Nord who believes in the simple pleasures of life - namely good drink and honest work. He maintains a positive outlook despite his domestic troubles, freely sharing his thoughts and life philosophy with others. While hardworking and responsible during business hours, he shows a clear preference for spending his evenings drinking rather than at home.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. His hands are calloused from years of working with lumber and axes, and his skin shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors year-round.', '* Olda - His wife, whom he considers spiteful and cold-hearted * Lodvar - His brother who lives with him and helps at the mill * Local Inn Patrons - Regular drinking companions and friends * Local Traders - Business relationships for lumber sales', 'Horgeir owns and operates the Dragon Bridge lumber mill, managing both the business aspects and performing the physical labor of cutting and processing lumber. His mill serves as a vital source of building materials for the region, particularly during the civil war when demand has increased significantly.', '* Expert woodcutter with deep knowledge of lumber processing * Proficient with axes, both for woodcutting and self-defense * Business management and trading expertise * Physical strength and stamina from years of manual labor', 'Speaks in a friendly, straightforward manner typical of Nordic workers, often peppering his speech with references to drinking and complaints about his wife. His tone is generally cheerful and welcoming, though becomes more bitter when discussing his marriage.', '* Maintain and expand his lumber mill business * Find personal happiness despite his troubled marriage * Continue providing essential lumber supplies to both sides of the civil war * Preserve enough wealth to ensure a comfortable retirement');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('horik_halfhand', 'Horik Halfhand is a stoic Nord warrior and retired Imperial Legionnaire who serves as the devoted protector of his former commander, Brina Merilis, in Dawnstar. His unwavering loyalty and dedication to duty exemplify the disciplined military bearing of a lifelong soldier, maintaining his allegiance to the Empire despite living in Stormcloak-controlled territory.', 'nord, warrior, pale, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born on a farm to parents who died in his youth, Horik joined the Imperial Legion at a young age, finding his true family within its ranks. He has served under Brina Merilis for over 30 years, following her through numerous campaigns and eventually retiring with her to Dawnstar, where he continues his service as her unofficial guardian.', 'Horik is a man of few words and steadfast loyalty, maintaining a professional demeanor that masks deep personal dedication. His stoic nature and reluctance to discuss his past suggest someone who has found purpose in service rather than personal relationships, while his unwavering devotion to Brina hints at complex emotions beneath his disciplined exterior.', 'A weathered Nord warrior bearing the physical hallmarks of decades of military service, with a sturdy build and battle-hardened physique. His nickname ''Halfhand'' suggests a possible old injury or distinctive feature of his hands, though the exact nature is unknown.', '* Brina Merilis - Former Legion commander and the focus of his unwavering loyalty * Imperial Legion - Former brothers-in-arms, maintaining strong ties despite retirement * Jarl Skald - Tense relationship due to opposing political allegiances * Dawnstar Guards - Professional but distant relationship as fellow warriors', 'While officially retired from the Imperial Legion, Horik serves as an unofficial bodyguard and companion to Brina Merilis. Should she become Jarl of the Pale, he assumes the formal position of her housecarl, continuing his lifelong service in an official capacity.', '* Veteran warrior trained in Imperial Legion combat techniques * Expert in sword and shield combat tactics * Skilled bodyguard with decades of experience protecting commanding officers * Proficient in military strategy and defensive tactics * Experienced in patrol and guard duty procedures', 'Horik speaks in brief, direct statements that reflect his military background and professional demeanor. His responses are typically short and to the point, showing deference when addressing Brina and maintaining formal speech patterns even in casual situations.', '* Protect and serve Brina Merilis until his dying day * Maintain Imperial influence in Dawnstar despite Stormcloak control * Uphold the values and traditions of the Imperial Legion in retirement * Support Brina''s potential rise to power as Jarl of the Pale');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('horm', 'Horm is a dedicated Nord stable hand who has spent his entire life working with and caring for horses at the Solitude Stables. His deep emotional connection to the horses under his care stems from childhood experiences, and he views them as extended family members rather than mere livestock.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised at Katla''s Farm, Horm learned the art of horse care from his father Geimund during both prosperous and lean times. His formative years were marked by a particularly difficult period when the family struggled to feed their horses, leading to his selfless act of sharing his own meals with them - a story he often recounts to demonstrate his lifelong dedication to equine care.', 'Horm is a hardworking, practical Nord who places the welfare of horses above all else. He demonstrates unwavering dedication to his duties and shows great empathy toward animals, though he can be somewhat abrupt with people when stable work demands his attention. His straightforward nature and single-minded focus on his work reflect both his Nord heritage and his specialized upbringing.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered complexion typical of someone who works outdoors year-round. His hands are calloused from years of manual labor, and his posture reflects the strength required for stable work. His features likely bear the characteristic Nord traits of his parents, tempered by constant exposure to Haafingar''s harsh coastal climate.', '* Geimund - Beloved father and mentor who taught him everything about horse care * Fridrika - Mother who helps maintain their household * Katla - Farm owner and employer who trusts the family with her stables * Grani - Favorite horse at the stables whom he frequently checks on', 'Horm serves as the assistant stable master at Solitude Stables, handling daily care of the horses including feeding, grooming, and exercise. Upon his father''s death, he assumes full responsibility as the primary horse merchant and stable master, continuing the family tradition of excellent equine care.', '* Expert horse trainer with deep understanding of equine behavior and needs * Skilled in basic veterinary care and horse maintenance * Capable of breaking in new horses and teaching riding basics * Proficient in stable management and business operations * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense', 'Horm speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of working-class Nords, often cutting conversations short to tend to his duties. His speech frequently includes references to horses and stable work, reflecting his singular focus on his profession.', '* Maintain the high standards of horse care established by his father at Solitude Stables * Ensure the financial stability of the family business to prevent another period of hardship * Expand the stables'' reputation as the premier horse merchant in Haafingar Hold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hreinn', 'Hreinn is a young Nord who works diligently at his family''s establishment, the Silver-Blood Inn in Markarth, caught between his quarreling parents'' constant disputes. Despite the challenging family dynamics, he maintains a strong work ethic and sense of duty, though he struggles to find his own identity amid his parents'' opposing expectations.', 'nord, innkeeper, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth to innkeepers Kleppr and Frabbi, Hreinn has spent his entire life within the stone walls of the Silver-Blood Inn. Growing up in an environment of constant parental conflict has shaped his reserved nature and work-focused mindset. His upbringing has been marked by his father''s encouraging but potentially misguided mentorship and his mother''s critical attitude toward his father''s influence.', 'Hreinn is an introverted and conscientious individual who takes his responsibilities seriously, often using work as an escape from family tension. He shows signs of anxiety and uncertainty about his future, particularly regarding relationships, as evidenced by his concerns about repeating his parents'' argumentative dynamic. Despite the challenging environment, he maintains a patient and diplomatic demeanor, carefully navigating between his warring parents.', 'A young Nord male with the characteristic sturdy build of his race, though perhaps slightly less muscular due to his indoor lifestyle. His features likely show signs of stress and fatigue from his demanding work schedule and family situation. His appearance is neat and well-maintained, reflecting his attention to detail in his work.', '* Kleppr - Father and mentor who believes in his potential as a future innkeeper * Frabbi - Mother who praises his work ethic while using it to criticize his father * Hroki - Sister and fellow worker at the inn, sharing similar family pressures * Inn Patrons - Professional but minimal interactions, keeping conversations brief', 'Hreinn serves as an assistant innkeeper at the Silver-Blood Inn, responsible for various essential tasks including cleaning linens, maintaining floors, and checking on guests. His role involves both customer service and maintenance duties, working long hours from early morning until evening.', '* Proficient in general inn maintenance and housekeeping * Experienced in guest relations and basic hospitality management * Capable of basic accounting and inventory management * Skilled at conflict avoidance and de-escalation', 'Hreinn speaks in brief, direct sentences, preferring to keep conversations short and focused on immediate tasks or concerns. His tone is typically quiet and reserved, reflecting his desire to avoid conflict.', '* Develop his innkeeping skills while maintaining peace between his parents * Eventually find a peaceful marriage unlike his parents'' relationship * Establish his own identity beyond the shadow of his parents'' conflicts * Potentially take over management of the inn in a way that would make both parents proud');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hrodulf', 'Hrodulf was a solitary Nord farmer whose life took a dark turn after discovering ancient Dwemer machinery operating beneath his house on Solstheim. His growing obsession with the mysterious mechanical sounds led to increasingly erratic behavior, ultimately contributing to both his death and that of his concerned lover, Bjornolfr.', 'nord, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally from Skyrim, Hrodulf established himself as a farmer on Solstheim, living in a modest house along the coast. His life was relatively peaceful until he began hearing the sounds of Dwemer machinery beneath his home, which gradually consumed his thoughts and led to his descent into obsession. Despite having a loving relationship with Bjornolfr in Solitude, he refused to leave his property, becoming increasingly isolated and fixated on the underground sounds.', 'Hrodulf was initially a practical and hardworking Nord farmer who transformed into an obsessive and paranoid individual due to his fixation with the Dwemer machinery. His stubborn nature and growing madness led him to ignore the concerned pleas of his lover, showing how deeply the mysterious sounds had affected his mental state. Despite his deteriorating condition, his journal entries reveal an intelligent mind attempting to understand the ancient technology beneath his home.', 'A typical Nord male with the weathered features of someone who spent considerable time working outdoors. His body shows signs of the physical labor required of a farmer, with callused hands and a sturdy build typical of his race.', '* Bjornolfr - Lover from Solitude who tried desperately to convince him to leave his home * Local farmers - Likely maintained trading relationships before his obsession took hold * Reavers - Hostile squatters who eventually occupied his home and killed Bjornolfr', 'Hrodulf worked as a farmer on Solstheim, maintaining his coastal property and likely growing crops suitable to the ash-laden soil of the island. His agricultural work was eventually neglected as his obsession with the Dwemer machinery grew stronger.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of agriculture and animal husbandry * Basic carpentry and home maintenance abilities * Survival skills necessary for living alone on Solstheim''s harsh coast * Amateur scholar of Dwemer machinery, though largely self-taught through observation', 'Based on his journal entries, Hrodulf''s speech became increasingly agitated and focused on the mechanical sounds, with frequent references to the constant noise and machinery beneath his house. His writing style suggests a descent from clear, rational thoughts to more scattered and obsessive patterns.', '* Understand the nature and purpose of the Dwemer machinery beneath his house * Document and study the mechanical sounds that consumed his attention * Maintain his solitary lifestyle despite pressure to leave his property');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hroggar', 'Hroggar is a Nord lumberjack from Morthal whose life took a dark turn after the suspicious death of his wife and daughter in a house fire. Currently enthralled by the vampire Alva, he exists in a state of magical servitude, having abandoned his grief and natural emotions for an artificial devotion to his manipulator.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally a simple family man and hardworking lumberjack in Morthal, Hroggar lived a quiet life with his wife and daughter Helgi until tragedy struck. After his family perished in a suspicious house fire, he immediately moved in with Alva, raising concerns among the townspeople. Unknown to him, Alva orchestrated the deaths of his family and placed him under vampiric thralldom.', 'Under Alva''s thrall, Hroggar displays an unnatural detachment from the deaths of his wife and daughter, showing no grief or remorse. He is fiercely protective of Alva''s home and hostile to intruders, demonstrating the single-minded devotion typical of a vampire''s thrall. His natural personality has been suppressed, though glimpses of his former melancholic and hardworking nature occasionally surface.', 'Hroggar is a sturdy Nord male with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. His face shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors, with callused hands from years of handling lumber. His movements are somewhat mechanical and rigid, characteristic of those under vampiric influence.', '* Alva - His vampiric manipulator whom he serves with unnatural devotion * Helgi - His deceased daughter, whose death he shows unnaturally little concern for * Thonnir - Fellow lumberjack at the mill, though their relationship is now strained * Jorgen - Coworker at the lumber mill who views him with suspicion * Townspeople of Morthal - Generally regard him with suspicion and concern', 'Hroggar works as a lumberjack at Morthal''s lumber mill, where he spends his days chopping wood alongside Thonnir and Jorgen. When not working, he serves as a guardian of Alva''s house, protecting it from intruders with zealous dedication due to his enthralled state.', '* Experienced lumberjack with extensive knowledge of woodcutting and lumber processing * Physically strong from years of manual labor * Capable with an axe both for woodcutting and combat * Basic home construction and maintenance abilities', 'Hroggar speaks in short, guarded sentences, often deflecting conversation about his past or current situation. His tone is flat and emotionless when discussing his deceased family, but becomes defensive and aggressive when Alva is mentioned.', '* Protect Alva and her home from any perceived threats (due to thralldom) * Continue his work at the lumber mill to maintain appearances * Avoid discussions about his past and the fate of his family');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hroki', 'Hroki is a privileged young Nord woman working at her family''s establishment, the Silver-Blood Inn in Markarth, who yearns for a more refined and luxurious lifestyle than her current station allows. Despite being born into a relatively comfortable merchant family, she struggles with the harsh realities of Skyrim''s frontier culture while pursuing her aspirations of sophistication and social elevation.', 'nord, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth to innkeepers Kleppr and Frabbi, Hroki grew up in relative comfort compared to many other citizens of the Reach. Her upbringing in the Silver-Blood Inn exposed her to wealthy travelers and merchants, fostering a taste for luxury and refinement that shaped her aspirations. Her father''s indulgent nature and willingness to provide spending money has reinforced her somewhat spoiled disposition.', 'Hroki exhibits a notably snobbish and entitled attitude, looking down on those she considers beneath her station while simultaneously yearning to associate with those of higher status. She is easily disgusted by the crude aspects of frontier life and shows particular disdain for anything she deems unrefined. Despite her haughty demeanor, she harbors deep insecurities about her social status and desperately seeks ways to distinguish herself from other common townsfolk.', 'A young Nord woman with the typical fair complexion of her race, likely in her early twenties. She maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting someone who aspires to upper-class status, though her features retain the hardy characteristics common to Nord women.', '* Kleppr - Father and innkeeper who indulges her with spending money * Frabbi - Mother and fellow innkeeper, often argues with Kleppr * Hreinn - Brother and co-worker at the inn * Hogni Red-Arm - Antagonistic relationship with the local meat vendor * Kerah - Friendly business relationship with the jewelry merchant * Silver-Blood Family - Respects and attempts to curry favor with Markarth''s ruling family', 'Hroki works as a server and general helper at the Silver-Blood Inn, performing various cleaning and serving duties throughout the day. Her position allows her significant free time to browse the marketplace, where she spends hours examining luxury goods and jewelry.', '* Basic hospitality and customer service abilities * Knowledgeable about jewelry and luxury goods * Capable of basic self-defense with a dagger * Experienced in inn-keeping duties and cleaning * Social networking among Markarth''s merchants', 'Hroki speaks with a haughty, often condescending tone that betrays her aspirations of nobility. Her vocabulary and manner of speech attempt to mirror those of higher social status, though her common background occasionally shows through.', '* Elevate her social status to match Markarth''s elite * Acquire unique and exotic jewelry and clothing to distinguish herself * Eventually marry into a wealthy or noble family * Distance herself from the common aspects of inn work');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hrongar', 'Hrongar is the fiercely traditional Nord brother and trusted advisor to Jarl Balgruuf the Greater of Whiterun. A proud warrior and passionate advocate for Nord customs, he serves as a counterbalance to the more cautious and diplomatic approaches of other advisors in Dragonsreach, particularly Proventus Avenicci.', 'nord, warrior, noble, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born into the noble family of Whiterun, Hrongar grew up alongside his brother Balgruuf, developing a deep appreciation for Nord traditions and martial prowess. His upbringing in Dragonsreach and exposure to political matters shaped his understanding of leadership, though he maintains a warrior''s perspective rather than a diplomat''s approach.', 'Hrongar is assertive, passionate, and sometimes hot-headed in his dedication to Nord traditions and customs. He shows unwavering loyalty to his brother and Whiterun, but often advocates for more aggressive and direct solutions to problems. His warrior''s mindset leads him to favor action over discussion, and he can be dismissive of those who don''t share his traditional Nord values.', 'A strong, muscular Nord male with the characteristic hardy build of a seasoned warrior. His features bear a familial resemblance to his brother Balgruuf, though his years of martial training have left him with a more athletic physique.', '* Balgruuf the Greater - Brother and Jarl, whom he serves with fierce loyalty * Proventus Avenicci - Rival advisor with whom he frequently disagrees * Adrianne Avenicci - Shows disdain for her influence over her father''s counsel * The Companions - Respects their warrior tradition and fighting prowess * Greybeards - Holds deep reverence for their ancient Nord wisdom', 'Hrongar serves as a courtier and military advisor to the Jarl of Whiterun, providing counsel on matters of defense and traditional Nord customs. His position in Dragonsreach allows him to influence important decisions regarding Whiterun''s military strategy and political alignments.', '* Masterful two-handed weapon combat, particularly with greatswords * Military tactical expertise and strategic planning abilities * Traditional Nord warrior training and combat techniques * Leadership and commanding presence in military matters * Knowledge of ancient Nord customs and traditions', 'Speaks with authority and conviction, often using direct and forceful language that reflects his warrior''s mindset. His speech frequently includes references to combat and action, demonstrating his preference for decisive movement over careful deliberation.', '* Protect Whiterun and maintain its strength through traditional Nord methods * Convince his brother to take a more aggressive stance in the civil war * Preserve and promote ancient Nord traditions and customs * See Whiterun''s military might expanded and strengthened');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hulda', 'Hulda is a hardworking Nord innkeeper who has spent decades running the prestigious Bannered Mare in Whiterun, establishing it as one of the city''s most popular gathering spots. Though dedicated to her establishment, she has grown weary of the demanding work and looks forward to retirement, having arranged to eventually sell the inn to the ambitious young merchant Ysolda.', 'nord, innkeeper, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun, Hulda worked her way up from a simple barmaid to eventually acquiring ownership of the Bannered Mare in her younger years. Through careful management and a strong work ethic, she transformed the establishment into one of Whiterun''s most respected institutions, serving as a hub for travelers, merchants, and locals alike for several decades.', 'Hulda is a practical and business-minded individual who takes pride in running an orderly establishment. While generally cordial to customers, she harbors some prejudiced views toward magic users and elves, displaying the typical Nord conservative attitudes. She shows a strong sense of duty to her position but has grown weary of the constant demands of innkeeping.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the sturdy build typical of her race, showing signs of age but maintaining a dignified bearing. Her face bears the subtle wrinkles of someone who has spent decades managing a busy establishment, while her hands show the calluses of regular physical work.', '* Ysolda - Potential buyer of the Bannered Mare, whom Hulda has chosen as her successor * Saadia - Employee and barmaid at the inn, whom Hulda treats with a maternal authority * Mikael - The inn''s resident bard, whose presence she tolerates for business purposes * Whiterun Guards - Maintains good relations to ensure order in her establishment * Jarl Balgruuf - Respects his authority and serves as an informal information gatherer', 'Hulda serves as both owner and primary innkeeper of the Bannered Mare, Whiterun''s premier inn and tavern. Her duties include managing employees, serving customers, maintaining inventory, renting rooms, and acting as an informal information broker for both the Jarl''s bounties and local gossip.', '* Experienced business manager with decades of inn-keeping expertise * Skilled at brewing mead and preparing traditional Nord cuisine * Proficient at gathering and disseminating local information and rumors * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Accomplished at maintaining order in a rowdy tavern environment', 'Speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord innkeepers, with a slight Whiterun accent. Her tone is business-like but can become dismissive when discussing magic or elves, reflecting her traditional Nord biases.', '* Successfully sell the Bannered Mare to Ysolda and ensure a smooth transition of ownership * Retire comfortably after years of dedicated service to Whiterun * Maintain the inn''s reputation as Whiterun''s finest establishment until her retirement');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hunroor', 'Hunroor is a legendary Nord warrior from the Second Era whose tragic tale of betrayal and eventual triumph led him to his rightful place in Sovngarde. A member of an ill-fated expedition seeking the Nordic afterlife, he now stands as one of the few named heroes in the Hall of Valor, his story serving as both a warning about treachery and a testament to the indomitable Nordic spirit.', 'nord, warrior, dragon', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born in the Second Era, Hunroor was a respected Nord warrior who, along with his companions Erlendr and Nikulas, undertook a legendary quest to find the path to Sovngarde. Their journey led them to Solstheim, where they were betrayed by the wizard Grimkell, who transformed them into stone pillars at Brodir Grove. Though their physical forms were trapped, their spirits were eventually freed when Ulfgar the Unending slew Grimkell, allowing them to finally reach their desired destination.', 'Hunroor embodies the archetypal Nordic warrior spirit - brave, determined, and fiercely loyal to his companions. Despite his tragic fate at the hands of Grimkell, he maintains an unwavering sense of honor and shows no bitterness, instead focusing on celebrating the warrior''s life in Sovngarde. His steadfast nature and commitment to the warrior''s path make him a respected figure among the souls in the Hall of Valor.', 'As a Nord warrior, Hunroor possesses the typical robust build and tall stature characteristic of his race. His physical form reflects years of combat and warrior training, with a muscular frame and battle-hardened demeanor. His features bear the weathered look of one who spent much of his mortal life adventuring in harsh conditions.', '* Erlendr - Close companion and fellow warrior on the quest to find Sovngarde * Nikulas - Trusted friend and companion who shared his fate at Brodir Grove * Grimkell - The treacherous wizard who betrayed and cursed him and his companions * Ulfgar the Unending - Revered avenger who slew Grimkell and helped free their spirits * Tsun - Respected shield-thane of Shor whom he now serves alongside in the Hall of Valor', 'In life, Hunroor was a renowned Nordic warrior and explorer. In death, he serves as one of the eternal champions in Shor''s Hall of Valor, where he stands ready to fight alongside other legendary warriors in the final battle of Alduin''s Wall. His presence in the Hall marks him as one of the most worthy Nordic warriors to have ever lived.', '* Master of Nordic combat techniques and traditional warrior arts * Exceptional physical strength and endurance developed through years of combat * Skilled navigator and explorer, particularly in harsh Nordic territories * Expert in traditional Nordic warfare tactics and strategy * Proficient in using various Nordic weapons and armor', 'Hunroor speaks with the formal, measured tone of an ancient Nordic warrior, using archaic expressions and traditional Nordic phrases. His voice carries the weight of his experiences and the pride of his position in Sovngarde, often speaking in a bold, confident manner befitting a hero of the Hall of Valor.', '* Uphold the warrior''s honor and traditions in the Hall of Valor * Prepare alongside fellow warriors for the final battle of Alduin''s Wall * Guide worthy warriors who enter Sovngarde to their rightful place among the honored dead * Preserve and share the cautionary tale of his mortal journey to prevent others from falling to similar betrayals');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hunter', 'A skilled wilderness survivalist who makes their living tracking and hunting game across Skyrim''s untamed lands. Living a solitary but purposeful life, they demonstrate exceptional prowess with the bow and maintain an honorable code of sustainable hunting practices, while showing willingness to aid travelers they encounter.', 'hunter, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in one of Skyrim''s rural holds, they learned hunting craft from an early age as a matter of survival and tradition. After years of apprenticeship under veteran hunters and countless hours stalking prey in the wilderness, they chose to fully embrace the nomadic hunter''s life rather than settle in a town or city.', 'Generally friendly and helpful to travelers, demonstrating a strong sense of honor and fair play in their hunting practices. Shows deep respect for nature and wildlife despite making their living from it, taking only what''s needed and using all parts of their prey. Maintains a pragmatic outlook on life, believing there''s enough bounty in nature for all if people aren''t greedy.', 'Weather-beaten and hardy, with calloused hands and keen eyes adapted to spotting movement at great distances. Their muscular but lean build reflects a life of constant physical activity and outdoor living. Shows the characteristic signs of someone who spends most of their time in the wilderness - tanned skin and a rugged constitution.', '* Fellow Hunters - Maintains loose alliance with other hunters, sharing information about game movements * Local Jarls - Complicated relationship due to hunting regulations and territory rights * Traveling Merchants - Regular trading partners for pelts and meat * Dogs - Often keeps loyal hunting hounds as companions * Poachers - Natural antagonists who violate sustainable hunting practices', 'Professional hunter who tracks, kills, and processes wildlife for sustenance and trade. Serves as an informal guardian of the wilderness, helping to maintain the balance of local ecosystems while providing valuable resources to nearby settlements.', '* Expert archer with precise aim and knowledge of vital target points * Master tracker capable of reading animal signs and predicting movement patterns * Skilled in wilderness survival and navigation * Proficient at skinning, butchering, and preserving meat * Experienced in setting and maintaining hunting camps', 'Speaks in a direct, practical manner with occasional use of hunting terminology and nature metaphors. Their voice carries the confident authority of someone who knows their craft well, while maintaining a friendly and helpful tone.', '* Maintain a sustainable hunting practice that preserves wildlife populations * Protect hunting territories from poachers and over-exploitation * Pass on traditional hunting knowledge to worthy apprentices * Earn enough to maintain their independent lifestyle');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('iddra', 'Iddra is a hardworking Nord innkeeper who manages the Braidwood Inn in Kynesgrove while raising her family. She represents the archetypal Nordic businesswoman, balancing commercial interests with traditional values and family responsibilities, while showing particular concern for her community''s wellbeing.', 'nord, innkeeper, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Kynesgrove, Iddra married Kjeld and established herself as the proprietor of the Braidwood Inn. She has built the establishment into a modest but reliable business while raising two children, demonstrating the strong work ethic typical of Nord society.', 'Iddra is a practical and diplomatic innkeeper who maintains a welcoming demeanor while carefully managing her business interests. She shows patience with difficult customers like Roggi Knot-Beard while still being firm about financial matters, and balances being a protective mother with allowing her children to develop independence.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the weathered features common to Skyrim''s working class. She bears the physical resilience typical of Nord women, with a strong frame suited to the daily physical demands of running an inn.', '* Kjeld - Her husband, who assists with the inn and takes over if anything happens to her * Kjeld the Younger - Her son, who she''s protective of while trying to teach responsibility * Froa - Her quiet daughter who takes after her temperament * Roggi Knot-Beard - A regular customer with concerning debt issues * Local Community - Generally positive relationships with Kynesgrove residents', 'Iddra serves as the primary innkeeper of the Braidwood Inn, managing all aspects of the business from 8am to 8pm daily. She handles room rentals, serves food and drink, maintains the facility, and acts as a merchant for travelers, making her establishment a crucial hub for Kynesgrove''s community and economy.', '* Experienced merchant with strong bartering and business management abilities * Proficient cook and brewer familiar with Nordic cuisine * Basic combat training for self-defense, as evidenced by her carried iron dagger * Strong interpersonal skills for managing customers and maintaining order', 'Iddra speaks in a warm, welcoming manner typical of Nord innkeepers, with a practical and direct communication style. Her speech reflects both her merchant background and traditional Nordic values, maintaining politeness while being clear about business matters.', '* Maintain a successful and reputable establishment that serves the Kynesgrove community * Raise her children to be responsible and successful members of Nordic society * Resolve outstanding debts owed to the inn while maintaining positive customer relationships * Ensure the inn''s continued prosperity for her family''s future');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('idesa_sadri', 'Idesa Sadri is a devoted Dark Elf nanny employed by the prestigious Cruel-Sea family in Windhelm, serving as primary caretaker to young Grimvar Cruel-Sea. She represents a rare example of a Dunmer who has secured a respected position within a Nordic household, though her role reflects the complex social dynamics of Windhelm''s racial segregation.', 'darkelf, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Born into the Sadri family, Idesa made her way to Windhelm with her brother Revyn during the Dunmer exodus from Morrowind following the Red Mountain''s eruption. Through determination and likely her natural affinity for childcare, she managed to secure a position within the Cruel-Sea household, elevating her social standing above many of her fellow Dunmer refugees.', 'Protective and nurturing by nature, Idesa takes her duties as a caretaker with utmost seriousness, often showing genuine concern for Grimvar''s physical and moral development. She maintains a delicate balance between being firm yet caring, and demonstrates strong moral principles in her attempts to shield her charge from negative influences while teaching him important life lessons about privilege and humility.', 'Idesa has the characteristic ash-grey skin and red eyes of her Dunmer race, with sharp, angular features typical of mer. She maintains a neat, professional appearance befitting her position in a noble household, with her dark hair likely kept tidy and practical for her daily duties.', '* Grimvar Cruel-Sea - Primary charge and ward whom she deeply cares for and protects * Revyn Sadri - Brother and fellow Windhelm merchant with whom she maintains close family ties * Torsten and Hillevi Cruel-Sea - Employers who trust her with their son''s care * Aventus Aretino - Source of concern due to his dark activities and potential influence on Grimvar', 'Idesa serves as the full-time nanny and caretaker for the Cruel-Sea family, specifically charged with the upbringing and education of young Grimvar Cruel-Sea. Her duties include supervising his daily activities, providing meals, offering guidance, and ensuring his safety and proper development.', '* Experienced childcare provider with strong nurturing abilities * Skilled in household management and domestic duties * Knowledgeable about proper etiquette and noble household protocols * Basic self-defense capabilities as evidenced by her carrying an iron dagger', 'Idesa speaks with the formal tone typical of a professional household servant, but often allows maternal warmth to color her words when addressing Grimvar. Her speech patterns reflect both her Dunmer heritage and her position in upper-class Nordic society.', '* Ensure Grimvar grows up to be a responsible and compassionate member of Windhelm society * Maintain her respected position within the Cruel-Sea household * Protect Grimvar from negative influences while teaching him important life lessons * Help bridge the cultural divide between Nords and Dunmer through her role');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jarl_idgrod_ravencrone', 'Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone is a mystically-gifted Nord ruler who governs Hjaalmarch through a combination of political acumen and prophetic visions. Despite her elderly age, she maintains a sharp mind and strong connection to the divine, using her supernatural insights to guide her leadership decisions while carefully maintaining Imperial allegiance during Skyrim''s civil war.', 'nord, witch, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born into a long line of mystics in Hjaalmarch, Idgrod developed her prophetic abilities at a young age and was groomed for leadership of Morthal. Her visions and connection to the divine helped her rise to the position of Jarl, though some citizens remain skeptical of her supernatural guidance. She has witnessed her hold''s struggles through decades of hardship while raising children who share her gift of foresight.', 'Idgrod is contemplative and philosophical, often speaking in riddles and metaphors that reflect her mystic nature. She maintains a calm demeanor even in crisis, trusting in her visions while showing remarkable patience with those who doubt her abilities. Though appearing aloof at times, she deeply cares for her people''s wellbeing and works to protect them from both mundane and supernatural threats.', 'An elderly Nord woman with deep wrinkles and weathered features that speak to her advanced age and wisdom. Her sharp, piercing eyes seem to look beyond the physical realm, while her thin frame belies an inner strength and dignity. Her face often bears an expression of deep thought or distant concentration, suggesting her regular communion with prophetic visions.', '* Aslfur - Devoted husband and steward who helps manage daily hold operations * Idgrod the Younger - Daughter who shares her gift of foresight * Joric - Young son who struggles with prophetic visions * Imperial Legion - Cautious but steady allies in the civil war * Citizens of Morthal - Mixed relationships, some respectful while others doubt her methods', 'As Jarl of Hjaalmarch, Idgrod manages the political, economic, and social affairs of her hold from her seat in Morthal. She combines traditional leadership duties with mystical guidance, using her visions to make decisions that affect her people''s lives while maintaining diplomatic relations with both Imperial forces and local powers.', '* Powerful prophetic abilities and communication with divine forces * Skilled politician and diplomatic negotiator * Advanced knowledge of mystical arts and supernatural phenomena * Experienced administrator with decades of leadership experience * Natural ability to sense dangers and threats to her hold', 'Speaks with a measured, philosophical tone, often delivering cryptic observations and prophecies in a distinctive Nordic accent. Her words carry weight and wisdom, frequently incorporating metaphysical references and mystical insights that reflect her connection to the divine.', '* Protect Hjaalmarch and its people from both mundane and supernatural threats * Guide her children in managing their inherited prophetic abilities * Maintain peace and stability in her hold during the civil war * Preserve the mystical traditions of Morthal for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('idgrod_the_younger', 'Idgrod the Younger is a gifted Nord sorceress and heir to the Jarldom of Morthal, possessing the same prophetic abilities as her mother Idgrod Ravencrone. She stands as a bridge between the mystical and mundane aspects of Morthal''s leadership, balancing her responsibilities as a caretaker to her troubled brother with her development as a future leader and visionary.', 'nord, witch, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born into the ruling family of Morthal, Idgrod inherited her mother''s gift of supernatural foresight, though her abilities are still developing. She was raised in Highmoon Hall, where she learned both the art of leadership and the burden of dealing with supernatural abilities in a town already suspicious of magic. Her early life was marked by the challenge of helping care for her younger brother Joric, who struggles with similar prophetic abilities but has difficulty controlling them.', 'Idgrod demonstrates a mature and compassionate nature beyond her years, showing particular patience in caring for her troubled brother. She approaches her prophetic abilities with a balanced mixture of respect and caution, seeking to understand them while maintaining her practical duties. Despite the weight of her responsibilities and supernatural burden, she maintains a gentle demeanor and shows genuine concern for her town''s people.', 'A young Nord woman in her early twenties with the characteristic strong features of her race, though softened by a thoughtful expression. She bears a strong resemblance to her mother Idgrod Ravencrone, sharing the same dark hair and penetrating gaze that marks those with the gift of foresight.', '* Idgrod Ravencrone - Mother and mentor, teaching her about both leadership and handling prophetic visions * Aslfur - Father and steward of Morthal, provides practical guidance in governance * Joric - Younger brother whom she protects and cares for, sharing a unique bond over their supernatural abilities * Lami - Close friend and confidante, offers guidance and herbal remedies * Citizens of Morthal - Generally respectful but somewhat wary due to her family''s mystical reputation', 'As the daughter of Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone, she serves as an unofficial advisor in Highmoon Hall while preparing for her future role as Jarl. Her primary duties include caring for her brother Joric and learning both the practical and mystical aspects of leadership that will be required of her position.', '* Developing prophetic abilities inherited from her mother''s bloodline * Growing knowledge of political leadership and governance * Understanding of alchemical properties through her friendship with Lami * Basic magical aptitude, particularly in divination and foresight * Diplomatic skills and ability to mediate between different factions in Morthal', 'She speaks with a thoughtful, measured tone that reflects both her Nord heritage and her mystical nature. Her vocabulary is refined yet accessible, befitting her role as future leader while maintaining connection with common folk.', '* Master her prophetic abilities while maintaining balance with practical leadership skills * Protect and help her brother Joric cope with his own supernatural gifts * Prepare herself to eventually take over as Jarl of Morthal * Bridge the gap between the supernatural and mundane aspects of Morthal''s governance * Earn the full trust and respect of Morthal''s citizens despite their wariness of mystical abilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('idolaf_battle-born', 'Idolaf Battle-Born is a proud Nord warrior and influential member of the Battle-Born clan who stands as one of Whiterun''s most vocal supporters of the Empire. His fierce loyalty to both family and Empire, combined with his role in the ongoing feud with the Gray-Manes, makes him a controversial but significant figure in Whiterun''s political landscape.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, legion', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born into the prestigious Battle-Born clan, Idolaf was raised in Whiterun''s upper district among the city''s nobility. He grew up alongside Avulstein Gray-Mane as childhood best friends before the Civil War drove their families apart. His upbringing emphasized Imperial values and tradition, leading him to become one of the strongest advocates for the Empire in Whiterun.', 'Idolaf is confrontational, passionate, and uncompromising in his beliefs, often forcing others to choose sides in conflicts. While outwardly aggressive and militant in his Imperial support, he harbors complex emotions about the civil war''s impact on former friendships. His fierce loyalty to family and cause often manifests as self-righteousness and inflexibility.', 'A sturdy Nord warrior with the characteristic robust build of his race, Idolaf maintains a militant bearing that reflects his Imperial allegiance. His features are sharp and stern, weathered by years of training and patrol, with the proud posture typical of Whiterun''s nobility.', '* Olfrid Battle-Born - Father and patriarch of the clan, whom he strongly supports * Jon Battle-Born - Cousin who secretly courts Olfina Gray-Mane * Avulstein Gray-Mane - Former childhood best friend turned bitter enemy * Imperial Legion - Strong supporter and unofficial representative in Whiterun * Gray-Mane Family - Sworn enemies in the ongoing clan feud', 'As a prominent member of the Battle-Born clan, Idolaf serves as both a warrior and political representative for his family''s interests in Whiterun. He actively works to maintain Imperial influence in the city while managing his family''s business interests and military connections.', '* Trained warrior proficient with one-handed weapons and light armor * Experienced in Imperial military tactics and combat techniques * Political negotiator representing Battle-Born interests * Knowledge of Whiterun''s merchant networks and trade relations', 'Idolaf speaks in a direct, confrontational manner with a strong Nordic accent, often using Imperial military terminology. His speech is characterized by passionate declarations of loyalty to the Empire and frequent challenges to others to declare their allegiance.', '* Maintain and strengthen Imperial control over Whiterun * Defeat the Stormcloak rebellion and eliminate their influence in the city * Preserve the Battle-Born clan''s political and economic dominance * Suppress Gray-Mane influence and prove their family''s superiority');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('igmund', 'Igmund is the Imperial-aligned Jarl of Markarth who inherited his position after the Forsworn murdered his father Hrolfdir. A pragmatic ruler caught between tradition and political necessity, he continues his father''s policies of maintaining peace with the Empire and Thalmor while struggling to contain the ongoing Forsworn threat in the Reach.', 'nord, noble, falkreath, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born to Jarl Hrolfdir of Markarth, Igmund witnessed his city fall to the Forsworn during the Great War when Imperial forces withdrew. After his father made a controversial deal with Ulfric Stormcloak to reclaim the city, the subsequent Thalmor pressure forced them to arrest Ulfric and his militia. Following his father''s murder by the Forsworn, Igmund inherited the Jarlship and maintained the pro-Imperial stance, believing it necessary for peace.', 'Igmund is a pragmatic and sometimes world-weary ruler who places practical necessity above idealism. While proud of his Nordic heritage, he believes maintaining Imperial authority is crucial for stability and peace. He carries the emotional weight of his father''s controversial decisions and death, making him particularly focused on eliminating the Forsworn threat.', 'A middle-aged Nord male with the strong build typical of his race, though somewhat softened by his years of courtly living. His face bears the weathered features and stern expression common to Nordic nobility, with hints of stress and worry lines around his eyes.', '* Raerek - Uncle and steward, trusted advisor in matters of court * Faleen - Housecarl and protector, loyal defender of his court * Thongvor Silver-Blood - Political rival who seeks to replace him as Jarl * Forsworn - Bitter enemies who murdered his father and threaten his hold * Imperial Legion - Key allies in maintaining his power and defending the Reach * Thalmor - Uncomfortable but necessary diplomatic relations', 'As Jarl of Markarth, Igmund serves as the primary ruler and administrator of the Reach, one of Skyrim''s nine holds. He manages the region''s political, economic, and military affairs while maintaining order in the most troubled and contested hold in Skyrim.', '* Competent warrior trained in traditional Nordic combat styles * Diplomatic experience in managing various political factions * Administrative capability in governing a major hold * Strategic thinking in military and political matters * Knowledge of Nordic law and tradition', 'Speaks with the formal authority expected of a Jarl, often emphasizing his lineage and position. Uses direct, commanding language tempered with diplomatic courtesy when necessary.', '* Eliminate the Forsworn threat and bring lasting peace to the Reach * Maintain Imperial control over Markarth against Stormcloak ambitions * Preserve his father''s legacy while avoiding his mistakes * Balance Nordic traditions with Imperial political necessities * Strengthen Markarth''s position as the economic center of western Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ilas-tei', 'Ilas-Tei was an ambitious but ill-fated Argonian apprentice at the College of Winterhold who met his demise during a dangerous magical experiment involving skeevers. His death in the frozen wastes near a Shrine of Talos stands as a stark reminder of the perils faced by aspiring mages who push the boundaries of magical research.', 'argonian, thief', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Born and raised in Black Marsh, Ilas-Tei journeyed to Skyrim seeking magical knowledge and eventually gained admission to the College of Winterhold. Under Phinis Gestor''s tutelage, he showed particular promise in Conjuration magic, though his fascination with experimental spellcraft and creature control ultimately proved fatal.', 'Driven by an insatiable curiosity about magical manipulation of living creatures, Ilas-Tei often pushed the boundaries of safe experimentation. His academic ambition was matched by a stubborn determination to prove himself, sometimes leading to reckless decision-making in pursuit of magical breakthrough.', 'A lean Argonian male with mottled green-gray scales and distinctive amber eyes typical of his race. His horns showed the weathering common to Argonians who spent significant time in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Phinis Gestor - Mentor and teacher who saw great potential in his abilities * Fellow College Apprentices - Maintained professional but distant relationships * College of Winterhold - Member in good standing until his disappearance * Local Nords - Experienced typical prejudice against Argonians common in Skyrim', 'Apprentice mage at the College of Winterhold, specializing in experimental magic and creature control. His studies focused primarily on the manipulation of lesser beings through combined Conjuration and Illusion magic.', '* Adept-level expertise in Conjuration magic * Growing proficiency in Illusion spells, particularly those affecting animal behavior * Basic understanding of Alteration magic, especially water-breathing techniques * Practical knowledge of alchemy and ingredient properties * Experienced in handling and controlling small creatures like skeevers', 'Spoke with the characteristic rasp of an Argonian, but adopted the formal academic language common to College mages. Often used technical magical terminology when discussing his research.', '* Master the art of creature control through innovative magical techniques * Develop new methods of combining Conjuration and Illusion magic * Earn recognition within the College for his experimental research * Prove that Argonians could excel in traditional Nordic magical institutions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ildari_sarothril', 'Ildari Sarothril is a vengeful Dark Elf conjurer and former apprentice of Master Neloth who survived a dangerous heartstone experiment that left her physically altered and mentally scarred. Her profound magical abilities and obsession with revenge have transformed her into a formidable threat, orchestrating attacks on Tel Mithryn through her mastery of ash spawn while plotting the downfall of her former mentor.', 'darkelf, mage, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Originally a promising apprentice to Master Neloth in Tel Mithryn, Ildari volunteered for experimental heartstone research that nearly killed her. Left for dead by Neloth after the failed experiment, she survived through unknown means and established herself at Highpoint Tower, where she began plotting her revenge. Her experience with the heartstone fundamentally changed her, granting her unique powers but also driving her toward obsession and madness.', 'Ildari is ruthless, vindictive, and consumed by her desire for revenge against Neloth, whom she blames for her near-death experience. She displays signs of megalomania and emotional instability, likely exacerbated by the heartstone embedded in her chest. Despite her mental state, she maintains enough clarity and intelligence to orchestrate complex magical attacks and manipulate ash spawn forces.', 'A Dark Elf woman with the characteristic red eyes and ashen skin of her race, though her complexion appears more sickly and gray than typical Dunmer. The most striking feature is the visible glow of the heartstone embedded in her chest, which pulses with an unnatural energy. Her body bears various scars from magical experiments.', '* Neloth - Former master turned bitter enemy after failed heartstone experiments * Tel Mithryn Inhabitants - Targets of her vengeful attacks * Ash Spawn - Magical constructs under her control * Various Dunmer Settlers - Likely former associates from before her transformation', 'Ildari operates as an independent mage and conjurer from her base in Highpoint Tower. She dedicates most of her time to magical research focused on ash spawn creation and control, while simultaneously plotting against Tel Mithryn and Neloth.', '* Master-level conjuration magic with expertise in ash spawn creation and control * Advanced destruction magic specializing in lightning and frost spells * Skilled in defensive magic including wards and flesh spells * Extensive knowledge of Telvanni magical practices and heartstone properties * Exceptional magical endurance due to heartstone enhancement', 'She speaks with bitter contempt and arrogance, often taunting her opponents with condescending remarks. Her voice carries both the refined accent of a educated Telvanni mage and the harsh edge of someone consumed by hatred.', '* Exact revenge on Neloth for abandoning her after the failed heartstone experiment * Destroy Tel Mithryn and everything Neloth has built * Perfect her mastery over ash spawn and heartstone magic * Prove herself superior to her former master through magical achievement');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('illdi', 'Illdi is a promising but deeply insecure Nord student at the Bards College in Solitude, particularly gifted with the flute. Despite her natural talent and dedication to music, she struggles with self-doubt and feelings of isolation within the prestigious institution, yearning for recognition while battling her own uncertainties.', 'nord, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Illdi showed musical aptitude from an early age, which eventually led her to pursue education at the prestigious Bards College. Her journey to become a bard likely involved significant personal sacrifice and determination, as admission to the College is highly selective. Her tendency toward self-doubt may stem from early experiences of criticism or high expectations from family or previous mentors.', 'Illdi is characterized by a gentle, sensitive nature combined with persistent self-doubt and social anxiety. Despite her genuine talent, she struggles with impostor syndrome and often assumes others dislike her. She shows remarkable creativity and desire to innovate, particularly in her interest in creating original compositions rather than just performing traditional pieces.', 'A young Nord woman with the characteristic fair complexion common to her race. She likely maintains a neat, presentable appearance as expected of a College student, though her demeanor often makes her attempt to physically minimize her presence in rooms. Her hands show the calluses typical of a dedicated flautist.', '* Dean Inge Six Fingers - Respected mentor figure, though Illdi often fears disappointing her * Giraud Gemane - Teacher who encourages her to study classical works * Evette San - Friendly acquaintance who shows concern for her comfort * Fellow students - Perceived distant relationships, though this may be colored by her insecurities', 'Student at the Bards College in Solitude, specializing in flute performance and musical composition. She occasionally performs at events to earn extra money, including high-profile gatherings like Thalmor parties. Her position requires daily practice, attendance at lectures, and working toward solo performances.', '* Accomplished flautist with particular talent for emotional expression * Developing composer with interest in creating original works * Trained in traditional Nordic bardic traditions and classical works * Basic performance skills including public speaking and stage presence * Competent in basic self-defense with an iron dagger', 'Illdi speaks softly and often hesitantly, frequently qualifying her statements with self-deprecating remarks. Her tone tends to be apologetic and uncertain, though it becomes more confident when discussing music theory or performance.', '* Complete her education at the Bards College successfully * Gain recognition and respect from her peers and teachers * Create original musical compositions that can stand alongside classical works * Overcome her social anxiety and build stronger relationships within the College * Develop enough confidence to perform her original works publicly');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('illia', 'Illia is a conflicted Imperial mage who breaks away from her coven''s dark practices when faced with her mother''s planned transformation into a hagraven. Despite her upbringing among witches, she demonstrates strong moral conviction and courage by choosing to stop the evil rituals she was raised to perform.', 'imperial, witch, mage, rift, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born into a coven of witches at Darklight Tower, Illia was raised by her mother Silvia to follow the dark arts and serve the hagravens. She spent her formative years learning destructive magic and witnessing increasingly disturbing rituals, eventually reaching a breaking point when her mother decided to undergo the transformation into a hagraven herself.', 'Illia is torn between familial loyalty and moral conscience, ultimately choosing to stand against evil despite the personal cost. She shows remarkable determination and bravery in facing her own mother, while carrying deep guilt over her past involvement with the coven. Though generally serious and reserved, she displays genuine warmth toward those who earn her trust.', 'Illia is a young Imperial woman with pale skin typical of someone who has spent most of their life inside dark towers. She has a slender build common to magic practitioners, with delicate features that belie her inner strength and resolve.', '* Silvia - Her mother whom she was forced to kill to prevent her transformation into a hagraven * Darklight Coven - Former associates whom she betrayed to stop their evil practices * Hagravens - Powerful beings she once served but now opposes * The Dragonborn - Potential ally who helps her stop her mother''s transformation', 'Illia serves as a battlemage and former witch of the Darklight Tower coven. After breaking away from the coven, she can become a companion to the Dragonborn or serve as a member of the Blades.', '* Master of frost-based destruction magic * Proficient in general destruction and conjuration spells * Skilled alchemist with knowledge of various potions and poisons * Experienced in witch covens'' ritualistic magic practices', 'Illia speaks with a measured, educated tone that reflects her magical training, though often tinged with guilt and remorse when discussing her past. Her vocabulary reveals her educated background, but her delivery can be hesitant when dealing with emotional subjects.', '* Atone for her past involvement in the dark arts and evil rituals * Prevent others from falling victim to hagraven ceremonies and witch covens * Find a new purpose in life after leaving behind everything she once knew * Master her magical abilities while avoiding the darker aspects of spellcraft');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imedhnain', 'Imedhnain is a dedicated Breton employee at Arnleif and Sons Trading Company in Markarth, serving as the store''s primary assistant and heir apparent. Despite his occasional absent-mindedness, he represents the living legacy of the store''s history, having worked there his entire life and maintaining strong connections to both its past under old Arnleif and its present under Lisbet''s management.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth, Imedhnain has spent his entire working life at Arnleif and Sons Trading Company, where he learned the trade directly from old Arnleif himself. His deep connection to the store and its founder has made him an invaluable asset, leading to his position as the designated successor should anything happen to the current owner, Lisbet.', 'Imedhnain is a diligent and loyal worker who takes pride in his role at the trading company, though he often displays moments of forgetfulness and distraction. He shows strong family values through his protective relationship with his cousin Cosnach, willing to stand up to his employer to defend him. Despite his competence in managing the store''s operations, he exhibits some self-doubt about potentially taking over full ownership.', 'A typical Breton of average height and build, with the characteristic high cheekbones and slightly pointed ears common to his race. His years of working in retail and handling shipments have given him capable hands and a sturdy frame, though his posture sometimes betrays his tendency to get lost in thought.', '* Lisbet - Current employer and owner of Arnleif and Sons Trading Company, shares a respectful but sometimes tense working relationship * Cosnach - Cousin whom he brought in to help with shipments, frequently defends despite his drinking habits * Old Arnleif (Deceased) - Former mentor and original owner of the store, holds his memory in high regard * Store Customers - Maintains cordial but professional relationships with regular patrons', 'Imedhnain serves as the primary assistant at Arnleif and Sons Trading Company, responsible for checking shipments, maintaining inventory, and supporting daily operations. He is also the designated successor to the business, positioning him to potentially become the owner and primary merchant.', '* Experienced in merchant trade and business operations * Knowledgeable in inventory management and shipment logistics * Basic combat ability with an iron dagger for self-defense * Skilled in business accounting and ledger maintenance', 'Speaks in a modest and sometimes uncertain manner, often trailing off when discussing misplaced items or interrupted tasks. His speech patterns reflect both his professional merchant background and his slightly scattered nature.', '* Maintain the legacy and success of Arnleif and Sons Trading Company * Support and protect his cousin Cosnach while helping him maintain employment * Improve his organizational skills to better serve the store * Eventually prove himself worthy of running the store should the responsibility fall to him');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imperial_archer', 'A disciplined and proficient Imperial Legion archer who embodies the precision and tactical expertise of the Empire''s ranged forces. Though less heavily armored than standard legionnaires, he serves as a vital support element, providing accurate covering fire and strategic battlefield control.', 'imperial, archer, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil''s heartland, he was trained from youth in the Imperial City''s archery academies before joining the Legion. His exceptional marksmanship caught the attention of his superiors, leading to specialized training in the Legion''s archer corps and eventual deployment to Skyrim during the civil war.', 'Methodical and composed, he approaches combat with calculated precision rather than brute force. Shows unwavering loyalty to the Empire and takes pride in his role as a specialized soldier, though maintains a professional demeanor even with allies. Values discipline and order above all, viewing the Stormcloak rebellion as a threat to Imperial stability.', 'Standing at average Imperial height with a lean, athletic build suited for mobility and quick positioning. Features the typical Imperial complexion with sharp, alert eyes developed from years of archery training. Bears several small scars on his forearms from bowstring practice.', '* Imperial Legion - Sworn member and loyal soldier * General Tullius - Respected commander and strategic leader * Fellow Archers - Close-knit brotherhood of specialized ranged units * Stormcloaks - Viewed as dangerous rebels threatening Imperial order * Local Imperial Garrisons - Professional working relationship with fellow soldiers', 'Serves as a specialized archer in the Imperial Legion, focusing on ranged combat support and tactical advantage in battle. Responsibilities include patrol duty, guard detail, and combat operations against Stormcloak forces.', '* Expert marksman with exceptional accuracy using Imperial bows * Trained in light armor mobility and positioning techniques * Proficient in battlefield tactics and unit coordination * Capable of basic melee combat with shield and dagger * Skilled in maintaining and repairing archery equipment', 'Speaks with formal military discipline, frequently using Imperial Legion terminology and maintaining professional courtesy. Often employs precise, tactical language when discussing combat situations or military matters.', '* Advance through the Imperial Legion''s specialist ranks * Help secure Imperial victory in Skyrim''s civil war * Protect Imperial interests and maintain order in assigned territories * Perfect his archery skills and tactical abilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imperial_captain', 'A stern and uncompromising Imperial officer who commands the Legion forces at Helgen during the attempted execution of Ulfric Stormcloak and other prisoners. Her unwavering dedication to military protocol and Imperial law makes her a formidable presence, even in the face of unprecedented chaos.', 'imperial, warrior, skyrimall, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Rising through the ranks of the Imperial Legion through strict adherence to protocol and unwavering loyalty, she earned her position as captain through years of dedicated service. Her experience in handling prisoner executions and maintaining order in occupied territories made her the natural choice to oversee the execution of Ulfric Stormcloak, though fate had other plans.', 'Rigid and authoritarian, the Imperial Captain embodies the strict military discipline of the Legion. She shows little patience for questioning of orders or protocol, as demonstrated by her dismissal of Hadvar''s concerns about the unlisted prisoner. Her inflexibility and dedication to procedure, while admirable in peaceful times, proves to be a potential liability during crisis situations.', 'A well-built Imperial woman with a weathered face bearing the marks of years of military service. Her posture is impeccably straight, reflecting her military bearing, with callused hands from years of wielding a sword. Her stern expression and sharp eyes convey authority and command presence.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior officer whom she serves with unwavering loyalty * Hadvar - Subordinate officer whose concerns she routinely dismisses * Imperial Legion Soldiers - Commands their respect through stern leadership * Stormcloak Prisoners - Views them as traitors deserving swift justice', 'Captain in the Imperial Legion, responsible for overseeing military operations and prisoner handling in Helgen. She commands a detachment of Imperial soldiers and maintains order during high-profile prisoner executions.', '* Experienced commander with expertise in military tactics and prisoner handling * Skilled heavy armor warrior trained in Imperial combat techniques * Proficient with one-handed weapons, particularly the Imperial sword * Natural leader with strong commanding presence and authority', 'Her speech is clipped, authoritative, and militaristic, favoring direct commands over lengthy explanation. She speaks with the confident tone of someone accustomed to immediate obedience, using formal Imperial military terminology.', '* Maintain order and Imperial authority in her jurisdiction * Execute prisoners efficiently according to military protocol * Advance within the Imperial Legion''s command structure * Suppress the Stormcloak rebellion through strict enforcement of Imperial law');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imperial_deserter', 'A former Imperial soldier who abandoned his post after the chaos at Helgen, now struggling with a severe addiction to Redwater Skooma. His descent from disciplined soldier to drug-dependent deserter represents the dark consequences of both trauma and substance abuse in Skyrim''s harsh reality.', 'imperial, mage, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Originally stationed near Helgen, he witnessed the dragon attack and barely escaped with his life. The trauma of that event, combined with a legitimate back injury, led him to seek relief through skooma. What began as self-medication for physical pain evolved into a devastating addiction that cost him his military career and sense of honor.', 'Once proud and dutiful, he now exhibits the characteristic behavior of a skooma addict - paranoid, defensive, and increasingly isolated. He attempts to justify his desertion and addiction through rationalization, but beneath his drug-addled exterior lies deep shame and self-loathing for abandoning his duties.', 'A middle-aged Imperial male with weathered features and the remnants of military bearing in his posture, though now notably diminished by his addiction. Dark circles under his bloodshot eyes and trembling hands betray his dependence on skooma, while his once-fit frame shows signs of deterioration.', '* Imperial Legion - Former employers, now hunting him as a deserter * Redwater Den Dealers - Current suppliers of his addiction * Fellow Skooma Addicts - Loose social connections formed through shared addiction * Player Character - Recognizes them from Helgen, causing anxiety about potential exposure', 'Former Imperial Legion soldier, now unemployed and spending his days in a drug-induced haze at Redwater Den. His military training and experience are wasted as he focuses solely on maintaining his skooma supply.', '* Military combat training from the Imperial Legion * Sword and shield combat techniques * Basic survival skills from military service * Knowledge of Imperial military protocols and procedures', 'His speech alternates between defensive justification when lucid and slurred, disjointed rambling when under skooma''s influence. He frequently interrupts himself and trails off mid-sentence, showing clear signs of drug-induced cognitive impairment.', '* Secure his next dose of Redwater Skooma * Avoid detection by Imperial Legion patrols * Find relief from his physical and psychological pain * Maintain the delusion that his situation is temporary');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imperial_general', 'A seasoned military commander in the Imperial Legion who has risen through the ranks through tactical brilliance and unwavering loyalty to the Empire. Despite being a hardened warrior, he maintains a strong code of honor and believes in the Empire''s role as a stabilizing force in Tamriel, viewing the civil war in Skyrim as a regrettable but necessary conflict to maintain peace and order.', 'imperial, warrior, noble, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born into a military family in Cyrodiil, he was groomed from youth for service in the Imperial Legion, attending the Imperial Military Academy in the Imperial City. He served with distinction during the Great War against the Aldmeri Dominion, though the signing of the White-Gold Concordat left him with complex feelings about the Empire''s compromise. His successful campaigns against bandits and rebels in Cyrodiil earned him rapid promotion and eventually assignment to Skyrim during the civil war.', 'Stern and disciplined, but not without compassion, understanding the heavy burden of command and the cost of war. Though loyal to the Empire, he privately struggles with the terms of the White-Gold Concordat while maintaining a professional facade. He values order and structure, believing that a unified Empire is the best hope for mankind''s survival against external threats.', 'A weathered Imperial man in his late forties, with a muscular build maintained through decades of military service. His face bears several battle scars, and his short-cropped grey hair and stern brown eyes reflect years of command experience. He stands straight-backed with perfect military posture, carrying himself with unmistakable authority.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior officer and tactical advisor * Legate Rikke - Trusted subordinate and local expert on Nord culture * Legion Officers - Commands their respect through fair treatment and tactical expertise * Local Jarls - Maintains diplomatic relationships to ensure Imperial support * Stormcloak Leaders - Regards them as misguided but worthy opponents', 'Serves as a high-ranking general in the Imperial Legion, responsible for coordinating military operations and maintaining Imperial control in his assigned hold. He oversees troop deployments, military strategy, and coordinates with local authorities while reporting directly to General Tullius.', '* Master tactician with extensive knowledge of military strategy and battlefield command * Skilled swordsman specializing in Imperial combat techniques * Proficient archer capable of leading troops in ranged warfare * Expert in military logistics and troop management * Diplomatic negotiator with experience in civilian-military relations', 'Speaks with a formal, authoritative tone typical of Imperial military officers, employing precise military terminology and maintaining professional decorum. His speech is commanding but measured, reflecting both his education and years of battlefield experience.', '* Secure Imperial victory in Skyrim''s civil war through minimal civilian casualties * Maintain stability and order in Imperial-controlled territories * Strengthen the Empire''s position while preserving honorable military traditions * Protect Imperial citizens and interests from both internal and external threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imperial_mage', 'A disciplined Imperial Legion battlemage who combines martial prowess with destructive magic, serving as a specialized combat support unit during the dragon crisis. Though relatively young in their magical career, they represent the Empire''s growing acceptance of magic in military operations, particularly in response to increasing magical threats.', 'imperial, mage, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born to a minor noble family in Cyrodiil, they showed early magical aptitude and received formal training at the Synod before choosing military service over academic pursuits. Their decision to join the Legion was influenced by both family tradition and a desire to apply magical knowledge in practical combat situations, leading to specialized training in destructive magic and battlefield support tactics.', 'Disciplined and methodical, approaching both magic and military duties with careful precision rather than raw power. They maintain a professional demeanor that reflects their noble upbringing and Imperial military training, though they occasionally display pride in their magical abilities. Shows particular interest in the practical applications of destruction magic in military scenarios.', 'Athletic build typical of Legion training, with callused hands from both spellcasting and weapons training. Clean-shaven with short-cropped dark hair maintained to military standards. Bears minor burn scars on their forearms from early magical training accidents.', '* Imperial Legion Command - Direct superior officers who value their magical combat support * Fellow Legion Mages - Small brotherhood of military spellcasters who share techniques * Helgen Garrison - Comrades stationed at the ill-fated outpost * General Tullius - Commanding officer who authorized expanded use of battlemages', 'Serves as a specialized combat mage within the Imperial Legion, focusing on battlefield support and defensive operations. Responsibilities include magical combat support, training other soldiers in basic magical defense, and maintaining magical barriers during sieges.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly fire-based combat spells * Proficient in Restoration magic for battlefield healing * Trained in light armor combat techniques * Basic sword fighting abilities as required by Legion standards * Tactical knowledge of military formations and strategy', 'Speaks with the formal diction of both noble upbringing and military training, frequently using magical terminology alongside military jargon. Maintains a commanding tone typical of Legion officers, though softens when discussing magical theory.', '* Advance within the Legion''s magical combat division * Prove the value of battlemages in modern military operations * Survive the growing dragon crisis while protecting Imperial interests * Develop new magical combat techniques for military application');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imperial_quartermaster', 'Marcus Valerius is a seasoned Imperial Quartermaster stationed in Skyrim''s military camps, responsible for ensuring the Legion''s troops remain well-equipped for battle. A former legionnaire turned logistics expert, he takes immense pride in maintaining the supply lines that keep the Empire''s forces combat-ready during the civil war.', 'imperial, blacksmith, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born to a middle-class merchant family in Cyrodiil, Marcus served fifteen years as a legionnaire before an injury in combat led to his reassignment as a quartermaster. His extensive experience in the field, combined with his family''s mercantile background, made him particularly suited for managing military supplies and equipment distribution. He was transferred to Skyrim when the civil war began, bringing his expertise to the challenging northern frontier.', 'Efficient and methodical, Marcus approaches his duties with military precision and unwavering dedication to Imperial protocol. Though gruff and businesslike on the surface, he harbors a deep concern for the wellbeing of the soldiers he supplies, often going to great lengths to procure specific items requested by troops. His years of service have left him with a cynical view of war, though he maintains absolute loyalty to the Empire.', 'A sturdy Imperial man in his mid-forties with a weathered face bearing a prominent scar across his left cheek. His short-cropped gray hair and militant posture reflect his military background, while his calloused hands show years of handling weapons and equipment. Standing at average height with a robust build, he maintains the physical fitness expected of Legion personnel.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior officer who oversees all military operations in Skyrim * Local Blacksmiths - Professional contacts for weapons and armor procurement * Imperial Legion Soldiers - Maintains professional relationships with troops he supplies * Traveling Merchants - Network of contacts for acquiring specialized equipment * Legate Rikke - Regular coordination for troop supply requirements', 'As Imperial Quartermaster, Marcus oversees the acquisition, storage, and distribution of military supplies for Imperial forces throughout Skyrim. He maintains detailed inventory records, coordinates with suppliers, and ensures that all equipment meets Legion standards before distribution to troops. His position requires him to manage a complex supply chain while dealing with the challenges of operating in hostile territory.', '* Expert in weapons and armor maintenance and quality assessment * Proficient in logistics management and supply chain operations * Skilled negotiator for procurement of military supplies * Competent swordsman from years of military service * Advanced knowledge of Imperial military regulations and procedures * Basic healing abilities from field medicine training', 'Speaks in clipped, efficient sentences with proper military terminology and occasional Latin phrases common to Imperial culture. His tone is authoritative and formal, though he occasionally softens when dealing with young recruits.', '* Maintain optimal supply lines for Imperial forces throughout Skyrim * Ensure the defeat of the Stormcloak rebellion through superior logistics * Train the next generation of quartermasters to uphold Imperial standards * Eventually retire to Cyrodiil with honor after seeing the civil war through');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imperial_soldier', 'A dedicated soldier in the Imperial Legion stationed throughout Skyrim during the civil war, representing the military might and authority of the Empire. This particular soldier is notable for being present at Helgen during Alduin''s attack and for executing the prisoner Lokir who attempted to flee.', 'imperial, warrior, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, he enlisted in the Imperial Legion at a young age, following a family tradition of military service. After completing rigorous training at the Imperial City, he was assigned to Skyrim to help quell the growing Stormcloak rebellion. Has served in multiple campaigns and garrisons across the province, witnessing firsthand the escalating tensions between the Empire and the rebel forces.', 'Disciplined and dutiful, adhering strictly to the Imperial chain of command and military protocols. Shows unwavering loyalty to the Empire while maintaining a professional demeanor, though occasionally reveals hints of war-weariness and pragmatic cynicism about the ongoing conflict. Generally treats civilians with respect but remains ever vigilant for signs of rebellion or dissent.', 'Athletic and well-built with the characteristic Imperial features including tanned skin and dark hair. Bears several small scars from previous battles, with calloused hands from years of weapons training. Maintains the clean-cut, regulation appearance expected of Legion soldiers.', '* General Tullius - Supreme commander who he serves with utmost loyalty * Legate Rikke - Direct superior officer who leads field operations * Fellow Legion Soldiers - Brothers and sisters in arms, forming tight bonds through shared combat * Stormcloaks - Sworn enemies who he faces regularly in battle * Local Nord Civilians - Complex relationship ranging from grateful supporters to hostile resistors', 'Serves as a frontline soldier in the Imperial Legion, participating in military operations across Skyrim. Duties include garrison defense, patrol duties, prisoner transport, and direct combat against Stormcloak forces. Also assists in maintaining Imperial control over held territories and supporting civil authorities when needed.', '* Extensively trained in Imperial Legion combat tactics and formations * Proficient with sword, shield, and bow as per standard Legion training * Experienced in siege warfare and fortress defense * Skilled in wilderness survival and cold weather operations * Basic knowledge of field medicine and battlefield first aid', 'Uses formal, military language with frequent references to Imperial protocol and chain of command. Often employs standard military terminology and maintains a respectful but authoritative tone, particularly when addressing civilians or suspected rebel sympathizers.', '* Maintain Imperial control over Skyrim and defeat the Stormcloak rebellion * Advance within the ranks of the Imperial Legion through dedicated service * Protect the citizens of Skyrim from dragons and other threats while upholding Imperial law * Eventually return to Cyrodiil with honor after completing his tour of duty');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('indara_caerellia', 'Indara Caerellia is a grieving Imperial mother and farmer in Falkreath whose life was shattered by the brutal death of her young daughter Lavinia at the hands of the werewolf Sinding. Despite her profound loss, she maintains a quiet dignity while supporting her husband and tending to their farm, finding solace in the spiritual guidance of Priest Runil.', 'imperial, peasant, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Indara relocated to Skyrim with her husband Mathies to establish Corpselight Farm in Falkreath. The couple worked hard to build a peaceful life and raise their daughter Lavinia, until tragedy struck when the child was killed by Sinding in a werewolf attack, forever altering their family''s trajectory.', 'Indara is a gentle and introspective soul, deeply affected by grief but maintaining an inner resilience. She finds meaning in tending to her farm and supporting her husband, while privately wrestling with the harsh realities of life in Skyrim. Despite her tragedy, she remains capable of showing kindness to others and appreciating the support of her community.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with the weathered hands and strong build of a longtime farmer. Her face shows signs of recent grief and countless hours working under the harsh Skyrim sun, with subtle worry lines around her eyes and mouth.', '* Mathies - Beloved husband and farming partner who shares her grief * Lavinia - Deceased daughter whose memory she honors daily * Runil - Respected town priest who provides spiritual comfort and guidance * Sinding - The werewolf who killed her daughter, source of deep trauma * Falkreath Community - Generally sympathetic neighbors who respect her family''s loss', 'Indara works as a farmer at Corpselight Farm, sharing agricultural duties with her husband Mathies. She tends to crops and maintains the farmland, though her daily routine has been impacted by her daughter''s death and her frequent visits to the cemetery.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Capable of basic food preparation and preservation * Skilled in basic herbalism and plant identification * Proficient in fundamental farm tool use and maintenance', 'Indara speaks softly and deliberately, with a melancholic undertone that reflects her grief. Her Imperial accent carries traces of her Cyrodilic origins, though tempered by years in Skyrim.', '* Find a way to process her grief and continue living despite her devastating loss * Maintain Corpselight Farm as a legacy to her daughter''s memory * Support her husband through their shared tragedy * Find peace with the harsh realities of life in Falkreath');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('indaryn', 'Indaryn is a Dark Elf brewmaster who manages the Black-Briar Meadery in Riften, serving as Maven Black-Briar''s appointed but powerless overseer. He represents the archetypal middle manager, caught between demanding superiors and unruly subordinates while struggling to maintain authority and productivity in a challenging work environment.', 'darkelf, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Indaryn relocated to Skyrim seeking better opportunities and eventually secured a position at the Black-Briar Meadery through unknown circumstances. His appointment as brewmaster by Maven Black-Briar initially seemed like a career advancement, but has proved to be a position of limited actual authority and considerable stress. Despite his title, he serves primarily as a figurehead while Maven maintains true control of operations.', 'Indaryn exhibits classic symptoms of burnout and impostor syndrome, constantly struggling to assert his authority while doubting his own leadership capabilities. He attempts to compensate for his perceived powerlessness through stern notes and threats to employees, though these are often ignored or mocked. His relationship with Haelga suggests a desire for comfort and validation outside of his professional struggles.', 'A middle-aged Dunmer with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race, showing signs of stress and fatigue in his face. His posture often reflects his mental state, alternating between attempted authoritative stiffness when supervising and a more defeated slouch during his off-hours.', '* Maven Black-Briar - His employer who maintains true control over the meadery while giving him little actual authority * Haelga - Romantic interest who provides comfort from his professional stress * Ungrien - Subordinate employee who runs the tasting room * Romlyn Dreth - Problematic employee who sells meadery products illegally * Talen-Jei - Innkeeper at the Bee and Barb who listens to his complaints', 'Serves as the brewmaster and overseer of the Black-Briar Meadery, responsible for maintaining production quotas and managing staff. Despite his title, his actual authority is severely limited by Maven Black-Briar''s direct control over all significant decisions.', '* Experienced brewmaster with knowledge of mead production and quality control * Basic business management and supervision capabilities * Moderate combat abilities typical of a Dunmer warrior * Administrative skills including inventory management and staff scheduling', 'Speaks in a stressed, defensive tone that alternates between attempts at authoritative command and exasperated complaints. His vocabulary and manner reflect his middle-management position, often using phrases that emphasize his supposed authority while betraying his actual powerlessness.', '* Prove his worth to Maven Black-Briar and gain more actual authority in the meadery * Establish genuine respect and control over his subordinates * Maintain the meadery''s profitability to secure his position and wealth * Find personal fulfillment beyond his professional struggles');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('indolent_farmer', 'The Indolent Farmer is a disillusioned Nord agriculturalist who turns to the Dark Brotherhood in a moment of desperate vengeance, performing the Black Sacrament to arrange the murder of someone who has wronged him. Despite his mundane occupation, he harbors deep-seated resentment and a willingness to embrace darker solutions to his problems.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in the agricultural community of Ivarstead, he inherited his family''s farmland and has worked the soil for decades. Years of dealing with harsh weather, poor yields, and possible personal betrayals have gradually eroded his once-optimistic outlook on life. His decision to contact the Dark Brotherhood marks a significant departure from his previously law-abiding existence.', 'True to his ''indolent'' nature, he displays a lackadaisical approach to his farming duties, preferring to spend time at the Vilemyr Inn rather than tending his fields. Despite his outward apathy, he harbors intense feelings of bitterness and revenge, which he carefully conceals beneath a facade of rural simplicity. His willingness to resort to murder suggests a moral flexibility at odds with his simple farmer appearance.', 'A weathered Nord of middle age, with calloused hands and sun-damaged skin from years of outdoor labor. His sturdy frame shows signs of physical work, though recent years of relative inactivity have left him somewhat soft around the middle. His face bears the creases and wrinkles typical of someone who spends long hours in the sun.', '* Wilhelm - Proprietor of Vilemyr Inn where he spends much of his time * Local Farmers - Strained relationships due to his reputation for laziness * Dark Brotherhood - Secret client relationship through the Black Sacrament * Unknown Target - Someone who has earned his murderous intentions', 'A farmer by trade, though his indolent nature suggests he performs the minimum work necessary to maintain his land. Spends more time avoiding his agricultural duties than attending to them, leading to a reputation for being workshy among the local farming community.', '* Basic agricultural knowledge and farming techniques * Sufficient literacy to read and perform the Black Sacrament ritual * Basic proficiency with farming tools and daggers * Knowledge of local geography and community gossip', 'Speaks in a plain, direct manner typical of rural Nords, with a tendency to be terse and to-the-point. His vocabulary is simple and unembellished, reflecting his farming background and limited education.', '* Achieve revenge against his chosen target through the Dark Brotherhood * Maintain his facade of being a simple, uninvolved farmer * Avoid any connection to or investigation of the upcoming murder * Eventually sell or abandon his failing farm');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('inge_six_fingers', 'Inge Six Fingers is a renowned elderly Imperial bard who serves as the Dean of Lute at the Bards College in Solitude, known for her exceptional musical talent and strict teaching methods. Her dedication to preserving bardic traditions and mastery of the eight-course lute has made her one of Skyrim''s most respected musical scholars.', 'imperial, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and raised in the Imperial City, Inge demonstrated prodigious musical talent from an early age, particularly with stringed instruments. Her nickname ''Six Fingers'' likely originated from her extraordinary dexterity with the lute, though some speculate she may actually have a subtle physical mutation. After decades of study and performance across Tamriel, she eventually settled at the Bards College, where she has taught for at least two decades.', 'Inge is strict, methodical, and unwavering in her dedication to musical excellence, often using stern teaching methods including the traditional knuckle-rapping with a wooden stick. She has little patience for mediocrity or laziness, believing that true mastery requires lifelong dedication. Despite her harsh exterior, she harbors a deep passion for preserving bardic history and traditions.', 'An elderly Imperial woman with weathered features and nimble, unusually long fingers that belie her advanced age. Her posture remains impeccably straight from years of proper musical form, and her hands show the calluses and strength of a lifetime of lute playing.', '* Viarmo - Superior and Headmaster of the Bards College * Ataf - Student under her tutelage * Illdi - Student under her tutelage * Jorn - Student under her tutelage * Aia Arria - Student under her tutelage * Pantea Ateia - Fellow instructor at the Bards College * Giraud Gemane - Colleague and Dean of History', 'As Dean of Lute at the Bards College, Inge is responsible for training aspiring bards in the art of lute playing and preserving the history of bardic music. She maintains a rigorous teaching schedule, conducting early morning classes and participating in various college educational activities throughout the day.', '* Master level expertise with the eight-course lute and other stringed instruments * Extensive knowledge of musical history and theory * Skilled instructor with decades of teaching experience * Expert understanding of bardic traditions and ancient musical techniques * Proficient in proper musical notation and composition', 'Direct and often brusque in her communication, favoring clear instruction over flowery language. Her speech carries the weight of authority and experience, typically delivered in a stern, no-nonsense tone that brooks no argument.', '* Recover and preserve important musical artifacts like Finn''s Lute * Train the next generation of master lutenists to maintain bardic traditions * Document and preserve ancient musical techniques and knowledge * Maintain the high standards of the Bards College''s musical education');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ingjard', 'Ingjard is a dedicated Nord warrior who joined the Dawnguard during their recruitment drive against the growing vampire menace. A skilled crossbow specialist and heavy weapons expert, she demonstrates unwavering commitment to protecting Skyrim''s people from supernatural threats through her service with the vampire hunters.', 'nord, warrior, rift, dawnguard, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim during troubled times, Ingjard likely grew up hearing tales of vampire attacks on settlements and witnessing the devastation they caused to communities. After learning of Isran''s reformed Dawnguard through traveling rumors and growing concerns about vampire activity, she made her way to Fort Dawnguard to offer her martial skills in service of protecting the innocent.', 'Ingjard exhibits the typical Nord traits of straightforwardness and martial pride, coupled with a strong sense of duty and pragmatism. She is observant and well-informed about current events, as evidenced by her awareness of rumors and ability to track developing threats. Her dedication to training and willingness to adapt to specialized weapons like the crossbow suggests a methodical and disciplined nature.', 'Ingjard possesses the sturdy build typical of Nord warriors, with a physique hardened by regular combat training and patrol duties. Her features bear the weathered look common to those who spend much time outdoors in Skyrim''s harsh climate. She moves with the measured confidence of an experienced fighter.', '* Isran - Respected commander and leader of the Dawnguard * Fellow Dawnguard Members - Comrades in arms united against the vampire threat * The Dragonborn - Potential ally and employer * Vampires - Sworn enemies to be hunted and destroyed', 'Ingjard serves as a full-time member of the Dawnguard, participating in regular patrols, training exercises, and vampire hunting missions. She is qualified to serve as a personal steward to landholding citizens of Skyrim, demonstrating additional skills in property management and household administration.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat and two-handed weapon techniques * Specialized training with Dawnguard crossbows and bolts * Proficient in vampire detection and combat tactics * Capable warrior able to handle both solo and group operations * Competent in property management and stewardship duties', 'Ingjard speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord warriors, with a focus on practical matters and current events. Her dialogue reflects both vigilance towards vampire threats and willingness to assist allies.', '* Protect Skyrim''s people from the growing vampire menace * Perfect her combat skills, particularly with Dawnguard weaponry * Serve the Dawnguard''s mission to eliminate vampire threats * Establish herself as a reliable warrior worthy of greater responsibilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ingrid', 'Ingrid is a passionate Nord food vendor in Helgen whose fierce Imperial loyalty and outspoken political views make her a notable presence in the community. Her strong convictions and vocal opposition to the Stormcloak rebellion reflect the deep political divisions running through Skyrim during the civil war.', 'nord, merchant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Helgen, Ingrid established herself as a successful food vendor through years of hard work and dedication. She witnessed firsthand the growing tensions between Imperials and Stormcloaks, which shaped her strong political stance and unwavering support for the Empire. Her marriage to Hert, a local mill worker, and the birth of their son Sonir further cemented her ties to the community and strengthened her desire for Imperial stability in Skyrim.', 'Ingrid is characterized by her fierce temperament and unwavering conviction in her political beliefs, never hesitating to voice her support for the Imperial cause. She possesses a strong sense of justice and community, though her passionate nature can sometimes lead to confrontational situations, especially regarding political matters. Despite her intense political views, she maintains a reputation as a reliable merchant and caring mother.', 'A sturdy Nord woman in her mid-thirties with the characteristic fair complexion and strong features of her race. She bears the weathered hands of someone who works with food daily, and her face shows the determination and resilience typical of Nord women.', '* Hert - Beloved husband who works at the Helgen mill * Sonir - Young son whom she fiercely protects * Imperial Guards - Allies and regular customers at her food stall * Stormcloak Sympathizers - Tense relationships marked by political disagreements * Local Helgen Residents - Generally positive business relationships despite political differences', 'As Helgen''s primary food vendor, Ingrid maintains a busy stall where she sells various prepared meals and ingredients to both townspeople and travelers. Her position puts her at the heart of the community''s daily life, allowing her to stay well-informed about local news and political developments.', '* Experienced food preparation and preservation techniques * Skilled haggling and business management * Basic self-defense with an iron dagger * Knowledge of local herbs and ingredients * Proficient in maintaining a merchant''s inventory', 'Ingrid speaks in a direct, passionate manner with a strong Nordic accent, often punctuating her speech with emotional outbursts when discussing political matters. Her vocabulary is that of a working-class merchant, practical and straightforward, but she''s not afraid to raise her voice when expressing her Imperial loyalty.', '* Maintain a successful business to provide for her family * Support the Imperial cause and see the Stormcloak rebellion defeated * Ensure a stable future for her son in a unified Empire * Expand her business once peace returns to Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ingun_black-briar', 'Ingun Black-Briar is a brilliant young Nord alchemist who stands apart from her family''s criminal enterprise, pursuing a darker fascination with the effects of potions and poisons on the living body. Despite her prestigious family name and wealth, she dedicates herself to the meticulous study of alchemy under Elgrim''s tutelage, harboring ambitions that lean toward the macabre.', 'nord, alchemist, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born into the wealthy and influential Black-Briar family of Riften, Ingun was raised in privilege but showed little interest in the family''s meadery business or political machinations. From an early age, she displayed an unusual fascination with alchemy and its effects on living beings, leading her to apprentice under Master Elgrim despite her mother''s disapproval.', 'Ingun is methodical, intelligent, and deeply absorbed in her alchemical pursuits, often appearing distant or preoccupied with her experiments. She displays a disturbing fascination with death and the fragility of life, viewing the body as an imperfect machine to be studied and manipulated. Though part of Riften''s elite, she shows little interest in wealth or status, instead finding satisfaction in her darker scientific pursuits.', 'A young Nord woman with the refined features characteristic of the Black-Briar family, showing signs of her privileged upbringing. Her hands bear the slight stains and calluses common to alchemists, despite her noble status. Her movements are precise and deliberate, reflecting her methodical nature.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Mother who disapproves of her alchemical pursuits but tolerates them * Hemming Black-Briar - Elder brother who focuses on the family business * Sibbi Black-Briar - Imprisoned brother with whom she has little contact * Elgrim - Alchemy master and mentor who recognizes her natural talent * Hafjorg - Elgrim''s wife who assists in her training', 'Apprentice alchemist at Elgrim''s Elixirs, where she spends most of her days studying and experimenting with various ingredients and their effects. Though technically an heir to the Black-Briar fortune, she shows little involvement in the family''s business operations.', '* Expert knowledge of alchemical properties and ingredient combinations * Specialized expertise in creating and studying poisons * Detailed understanding of anatomy and bodily functions * Capable of crafting complex potions and conducting careful experiments * Basic self-defense abilities with a dagger', 'Speaks in a formal, educated manner befitting her noble upbringing, but often drifts into technical alchemical terminology and disturbing observations about mortality. Her tone is typically distant and preoccupied, as if her mind is always partially focused on her experiments.', '* Master the art of alchemy and push its boundaries beyond conventional limits * Gain independence from her family''s influence to pursue her darker alchemical interests * Join darker circles where her talents might be better appreciated * Prove her worth to her mother through her alchemical achievements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('iona', 'Iona is a stalwart Nord warrior who serves as housecarl to the Thane of the Rift, embodying the traditional Nordic values of loyalty and martial prowess. She is a dedicated protector who takes her sworn duties seriously, willing to lay down her life to defend her Thane and their holdings in Riften.', 'nord, noble, warrior, rift, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born and raised in the Rift, Iona earned her position through years of loyal service to the Jarl''s court and demonstrating exceptional combat abilities. She underwent rigorous training in the traditional Nordic warrior arts and likely served in the Riften guard before being elevated to the prestigious position of housecarl. Her intimate knowledge of the Rift and its dangers makes her particularly valuable as a protector in this notoriously lawless hold.', 'Iona is stoic and duty-bound, taking her responsibilities as housecarl with utmost seriousness. She demonstrates unwavering loyalty and tends to be reserved in her personal interactions, though she can form strong bonds with those who earn her trust. Like many Nords, she values strength and honor above all else, but her time in Riften has also taught her to be watchful and suspicious of others'' motives.', 'Iona possesses the hardy build typical of Nord warriors, with strong shoulders and a muscular frame suited to wielding heavy weapons and armor. Her features are sharp and weathered from years of combat training and guard duty, with the pale complexion common to Nords. She keeps her hair practical and out of her face, befitting her militant lifestyle.', '* Jarl of Rift - Direct superior who appointed her as housecarl * Riften Guard - Former colleagues from her time serving the city * The Thane - Sworn to protect and serve them with her life * Maven Black-Briar - Cautious respect given Maven''s influence in Riften', 'As housecarl to the Thane of the Rift, Iona''s primary duty is to protect her Thane and their property at Honeyside. She serves as both a bodyguard and steward, managing the Thane''s household while being ready to defend against any threats. Her position is considered highly prestigious within Riften''s social hierarchy.', '* Expert in one-handed weapons, particularly skilled with war axes * Proficient in heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Trained in household management and stewardship * Knowledgeable about Riften''s political landscape and dangers * Capable archer and tracker', 'Iona speaks with the distinct Nordic accent and uses formal, respectful language when addressing her Thane. Her speech is direct and practical, focusing on matters of duty and security rather than idle conversation.', '* Serve and protect her Thane with unwavering loyalty and dedication * Maintain the security and reputation of Honeyside in Riften * Uphold Nordic traditions and values through her service * Prove herself worthy of the trust placed in her by the Jarl');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('irgnir', 'Irgnir is a hardworking Nord miner in Dawnstar whose life becomes increasingly troubled by supernatural nightmares plaguing the town. Despite her tough exterior as a seasoned miner, she emerges as one of the most vocal citizens about the dream crisis, showing both vulnerability and determination in seeking answers.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh climate of The Pale, Irgnir has spent most of her adult life working the mines of Dawnstar, eventually securing a position at Iron-Breaker Mine under Beitild''s management. Her years of labor have given her an intimate knowledge of mining operations and forged strong bonds with fellow miners, though she maintains a skeptical view of authority figures, particularly the Jarl.', 'Irgnir exhibits a complex personality combining working-class pragmatism with an underlying emotional sensitivity. Though generally serious and direct in her dealings with others, she shows a warmer side through her friendly banter with Fruki and confiding in Karl. The nightmare crisis reveals her more vulnerable aspects, as she struggles with fear while maintaining her strong-willed nature.', 'Irgnir possesses the sturdy build typical of Nord women, with strong arms and callused hands from years of mining work. Her features show the weathering effects of Dawnstar''s harsh climate and long hours working outdoors at the smelter.', '* Karl - Close confidant and trusted friend * Fruki - Fellow miner and friend despite working at competing mine * Beitild - Employer and mine owner, professional relationship * Erandur - Initially distrustful but eventually places faith in his ability to help * The Jarl - Maintains a skeptical and somewhat distrustful attitude', 'Irgnir works as a full-time miner at Iron-Breaker Mine, primarily operating the smelter and performing general mining duties. Her position requires long hours of physical labor and close cooperation with fellow miners, contributing to Dawnstar''s primary industry.', '* Experienced smelter operator with extensive knowledge of ore processing * Proficient in mining techniques and ore extraction * Physical endurance and strength from years of manual labor * Basic knowledge of local ore deposits and mining operations', 'Irgnir speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of working-class Nords, often expressing herself bluntly and with conviction. Her speech patterns become more agitated and insistent when discussing the nightmares plaguing Dawnstar.', '* Find a way to end the recurring nightmares plaguing herself and Dawnstar * Maintain her position and livelihood at Iron-Breaker Mine * Build a more secure future for herself in Dawnstar despite the current crisis');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('irileth', 'Irileth is a fiercely loyal Dark Elf who serves as housecarl to Jarl Balgruuf the Greater, having earned her position through years of fighting alongside him in battle. Her unwavering dedication to protecting Whiterun and its Jarl, combined with her considerable combat prowess and tactical mind, makes her one of the most respected figures in Dragonsreach.', 'darkelf, noble, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Born in Morrowind, Irileth left her homeland and eventually met Balgruuf when they were both younger warriors. They fought numerous battles together, forging a deep bond of trust and loyalty that transcended typical Nordic prejudices against Dark Elves. When Balgruuf became Jarl of Whiterun, she demanded to serve as his housecarl, a rare position for a Dunmer in Skyrim.', 'Irileth is stern, cautious, and deeply suspicious of outsiders, reflecting her paramount duty to protect the Jarl. She maintains a professional demeanor at all times, rarely showing emotion or engaging in casual conversation. Despite her initial distrust of newcomers, she can develop respect for those who prove their worth through actions rather than words.', 'A proud Dunmer with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her race, Irileth carries herself with a warrior''s bearing and alertness. Her face bears the weathered look of someone who has seen many battles, and her lean, athletic build speaks to her lifetime of martial training.', '* Jarl Balgruuf the Greater - Long-time friend and battle-companion turned liege lord * Proventus Avenicci - Professional colleague in Dragonsreach, though they often disagree on matters of security * Farengar Secret-Fire - Maintains a cordial working relationship as fellow members of the Jarl''s court * Whiterun Guards - Commands their respect as their superior officer and tactical leader', 'As housecarl to Jarl Balgruuf, Irileth serves as both his personal bodyguard and Whiterun''s chief of security. She oversees the city''s defensive operations, commands the guard force, and provides military counsel to the Jarl.', '* Master of both one-handed combat and archery, particularly skilled with sword and bow * Adept in Destruction magic, especially proficient with shock spells * Exceptional tactical and strategic military commander * Highly trained in personal protection and threat assessment * Possesses unique expertise in fighting dragons, with specialized magical resistance', 'Irileth speaks in a formal, authoritative manner with a slight Dunmeri accent, often using clipped, direct sentences that reflect her military background. Her tone is typically stern and businesslike, though she can be inspiring when rallying troops.', '* Ensure the continued safety and prosperity of Whiterun and its Jarl * Maintain the city''s defensive readiness against any threat, whether dragons, civil war, or other dangers * Prove through her service that Dark Elves can be trusted and valued members of Nordic society');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('irlof', 'Irlof is a seasoned Nord warrior and loyal crew member of the Blood Horkers under Captain Stig Salt-Plank''s command. A jovial and boisterous sailor who embodies the hearty Nordic spirit, he represents the more sociable face of piracy along Skyrim''s northern waters.', 'nord, warrior, sailor, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh northern coast, Irlof found his calling on the sea rather than in traditional Nord warrior pursuits. He joined the Blood Horkers after likely serving on various merchant vessels, finding brotherhood and purpose among the notorious pirate crew. His years of experience have made him a valued member of Stig Salt-Plank''s inner circle, trusted enough to accompany the captain during sensitive shore operations.', 'Irlof exhibits the classic Nordic love for celebration, mead, and camaraderie, often serving as the heart and soul of crew gatherings. Despite his profession as a pirate, he maintains a surprisingly cheerful and friendly demeanor, suggesting he views his work more as an adventure than malicious criminal activity. His loyalty to his crew and captain is unwavering, demonstrated by his willingness to follow Stig even when their activities are compromised.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of sailors who spend their days working ship rigging and cargo. Weather-beaten features and calloused hands speak to his years at sea, while his robust frame suggests someone equally capable of hefting cargo or wielding a weapon in combat.', '* Captain Stig Salt-Plank - Loyal crew member and trusted subordinate * Alding - Fellow Blood Horker crew member and drinking companion * Gjuk - Crew mate and partner in revelry * East Empire Company - Professional adversaries through piracy activities', 'Irlof serves as a core member of the Blood Horkers'' crew, participating in their piracy operations along Skyrim''s northern coast. His duties likely include sailing, fighting, and handling cargo during raids, while also serving as one of Captain Stig''s trusted men for special operations on land.', '* Experienced sailor with knowledge of seamanship and navigation * Competent warrior trained in Nordic combat styles * Proficient in boarding actions and ship-to-ship combat * Skilled at operating in cold maritime environments * Expert drinker with high tolerance for Nordic mead', 'Speaks with a thick Nordic accent and uses sailor''s vernacular, peppering his boisterous speech with maritime terminology and hearty laughter. His tone is generally warm and friendly, even when discussing potentially dangerous or illegal activities.', '* Maintain his position within the Blood Horker crew and continue their profitable operations * Eventually retire with enough wealth to open his own meadery or tavern * Follow Captain Stig to new opportunities in Hammerfell after their operations in Skyrim are compromised');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('irnskar_ironhand', 'Irnskar Ironhand is a formidable Nord warrior serving as the personal protector of Thane Bryling in Solitude, known for his stern demeanor and unwavering sense of duty. His reputation as a tough enforcer is balanced by his loyalty to his position and his role in maintaining order in the Blue Palace''s affairs.', 'nord, warrior, noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Rising from humble beginnings, Irnskar built his reputation through both legitimate combat and underground fighting circles, notorious for once breaking a man''s arm with a concealed horseshoe. His martial prowess and unwavering dedication eventually caught the attention of Thane Bryling, who appointed him as her personal protector, a position he has held with distinction for several years.', 'Irnskar is a gruff, no-nonsense individual who values directness and shows little patience for excuses or pleasantries. While outwardly harsh and uncompromising, particularly in matters of debt collection, he maintains a strong sense of duty and loyalty to Thane Bryling, though he''s not afraid to disagree with her more lenient approaches.', 'A imposing Nord male with the battle-hardened physique typical of a seasoned warrior. His face bears the scars of countless fights, with stern features and calculating eyes that reflect years of combat experience.', '* Thane Bryling - Employer and protected charge, shares a respectful but sometimes conflicting relationship * Octieve San - Debtor who owes him a substantial gambling debt * Endarie - Professional acquaintance who provides clothing for Thane Bryling * Local Guards - Maintains professional working relationships as part of his security duties', 'Serves as the personal protector to Thane Bryling, responsible for her security and handling various matters of enforcement. His position requires him to maintain order in Bryling''s affairs and act as an intimidating presence when needed.', '* Exceptional hand-to-hand combat abilities, particularly in unarmed fighting * Skilled with traditional Nordic weapons and armor * Experienced in intimidation and enforcement techniques * Knowledgeable in security protocols and protective services * Strategic thinking and threat assessment expertise', 'Speaks in a direct, often brusque manner with little concern for social niceties. His vocabulary is straightforward and practical, often delivering stern warnings or matter-of-fact statements with a thick Nordic accent.', '* Maintain and enhance his reputation as an effective enforcer and protector * Ensure the safety and security of Thane Bryling * Collect outstanding debts owed to him * Uphold order and stability in Solitude''s noble quarter');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('isabelle_rolaine', 'Isabelle Rolaine was a talented Breton sorceress whose tragic end came in Hob''s Fall Cave while attempting a desperate heist to resolve her financial troubles. Despite her magical prowess and connection to the Thieves Guild, her final decision to attempt a dangerous theft while intoxicated led to her untimely death, leaving behind a grieving lover and an undelivered letter explaining her intentions.', 'breton, mage, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Isabelle developed her magical abilities at a young age and eventually made her way to Skyrim seeking opportunity. She settled in Winterhold, where she fell in love with a Nord named Ranmir, but their relationship became strained by mounting financial difficulties. Her past association with the Thieves Guild through her friend Vex suggested a history of occasional thievery alongside her magical pursuits.', 'Isabelle was a complex individual who balanced magical talent with a tendency toward risky behavior, especially when under stress. While deeply caring and loyal to those she loved, she showed impulsive tendencies and poor judgment when desperate, particularly in her reliance on alcohol to boost her courage. Her final letter reveals both her practical nature in seeking solutions to problems and her emotional depth in expressing concern for her lover''s wellbeing.', 'A young Breton woman with the characteristic slight build and medium height of her race. Her features showed the refined bone structure common to Bretons, though years of hard living in Skyrim''s harsh climate had begun to weather her appearance.', '* Ranmir - Lover and partner, for whom she ultimately risked her life * Vex - Old friend from the Thieves Guild who provided her final tip * Winterhold Community - Casual acquaintances who knew her as Ranmir''s partner * Thieves Guild - Past association, though not a full member', 'Isabelle worked primarily as a freelance sorceress, likely taking odd jobs that required magical expertise. She supplemented her income with occasional thievery, though this appeared to be out of necessity rather than professional commitment.', '* Accomplished practitioner of magical arts, particularly in sorcery * Basic proficiency in stealth and lockpicking * Knowledge of alchemy and potion-making * Experienced in survival skills necessary for Skyrim''s harsh climate', 'Based on her letter to Ranmir, Isabelle spoke with a educated yet practical manner, showing both intelligence and emotional warmth. Her writing suggests she was articulate and direct, though capable of expressing deep sentiment when needed.', '* Secure financial stability for herself and Ranmir * Build a stable life in Winterhold with her lover * Advance her magical studies while maintaining a practical income * Clear any debts and achieve independence from criminal activities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('isran', 'Isran is the stern and uncompromising leader of the Dawnguard, a specialized organization dedicated to hunting vampires across Skyrim. A former Vigilant of Stendarr turned vampire hunter, he rebuilt the ancient order from ruins, driven by an unwavering conviction that vampires pose an existential threat to humanity.', 'redguard, warrior, rift, dawnguard, vampire', '', '', 'sk_isran', '', 'Originally trained as a Vigilant of Stendarr, Isran left the order due to disagreements over their methods and what he saw as their complacency regarding the vampire threat. His warnings about growing vampire activity went unheeded by the Vigilants, leading to their eventual destruction - a vindication that brought him no joy. After leaving the Vigilants, he took it upon himself to rebuild the ancient Dawnguard, establishing their base in the abandoned Fort Dawnguard in the Rift.', 'Isran is characterized by his intense paranoia, unwavering dedication, and absolute intolerance of vampires. He maintains a gruff, no-nonsense demeanor and shows deep skepticism toward outsiders, though he will reluctantly accept help when necessary. Despite his harsh exterior, he demonstrates genuine concern for his followers'' safety and the greater good of Skyrim, though his methods and attitude often alienate potential allies.', 'A weathered Redguard with dark skin and a bald head, Isran possesses a powerful, muscular build suited to wielding heavy weapons and armor. His face bears the scars of countless battles, with intense eyes that seem to constantly scan for threats, while his rigid posture reflects his military discipline and ever-vigilant nature.', '* Vigilants of Stendarr - Former associates, relationship ended in bitter disagreement * Celann - Former companion from his Vigilant days who rejoined him in the Dawnguard * Sorine Jurard - Recruited specialist in Dwemer technology * Gunmar - Recruited beast expert and valuable ally * Florentius Baenius - Recruited healer, though Isran finds his religious fervor trying * Vampires - Sworn enemies he has dedicated his life to destroying', 'Isran serves as both the founder and leader of the reformed Dawnguard, managing their operations from Fort Dawnguard. He personally oversees recruitment, training, and strategic planning while also serving as a master trainer in Heavy Armor for those who earn his trust.', '* Master-level expertise in Heavy Armor combat techniques * Highly skilled in two-handed weapon combat, particularly with warhammers * Proficient in Restoration magic, especially anti-undead spells like Stendarr''s Aura * Expert tactician and military commander * Skilled blacksmith and armorer specialized in anti-vampire weaponry', 'Isran speaks in direct, often harsh tones, favoring blunt statements and cutting straight to the point without social niceties. His voice carries both authority and barely-contained contempt when discussing vampires or those he distrusts.', '* Eradicate the vampire menace from Skyrim and beyond * Build the Dawnguard into a powerful and respected fighting force * Protect Skyrim''s population from vampire threats * Prove the validity of his warnings about vampire dangers to those who doubted him * Maintain constant vigilance against vampire infiltration and corruption');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('istar_cairn-breaker', 'Istar Cairn-Breaker is a hardened Nord commander who leads the Stormcloak forces in the Haafingar region with unwavering dedication to Ulfric''s cause. A fervent nationalist and tactical leader, he embodies the Stormcloaks'' vision of a free Skyrim, combining military discipline with deeply-held beliefs about Nord supremacy and independence.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh northern holds, Istar earned his surname ''Cairn-breaker'' through his renowned ability to navigate treacherous mountain passes and destroy Imperial supply caches hidden among Nordic burial sites. He rose through Stormcloak ranks through a combination of martial prowess and fierce loyalty to Nord traditions, eventually earning Ulfric''s trust to command the strategically crucial Haafingar camp.', 'Istar is a stern and uncompromising military commander who views the world through a stark lens of loyalty versus betrayal. His passionate nationalism borders on xenophobia, particularly regarding elves and Imperial sympathizers, while his devotion to Ulfric and the Stormcloak cause approaches religious fervor. Despite his harsh views, he maintains a strong sense of Nord honor and treats his soldiers with respect.', 'A towering Nord with weather-beaten features and numerous battle scars earned from years of warfare. His muscular frame and calloused hands speak to a lifetime of wielding heavy weapons, while his sharp eyes constantly scan his surroundings with military precision.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Revered leader and true High King in Istar''s eyes * Galmar Stone-Fist - Superior officer and respected military commander * Haafingar Stormcloak Soldiers - Loyal troops under his direct command * Imperial Legion - Sworn enemies seen as betrayers of Skyrim * Thalmor - Despised enemies representing everything he fights against', 'As commanding officer of the Haafingar Stormcloak Camp, Istar oversees all military operations in the region and coordinates attacks against Imperial forces. He manages troop deployments, maintains camp discipline, and serves as a direct representative of Ulfric''s authority in the hold.', '* Expert tactical commander with extensive knowledge of Haafingar''s terrain * Accomplished warrior proficient with both one-handed and two-handed weapons * Skilled archer capable of leading ranged assault operations * Natural leader with ability to inspire troops and maintain morale * Experienced survivalist adapted to Skyrim''s harsh conditions', 'Speaks in a gruff, authoritative tone with a thick Nordic accent, often incorporating traditional Nord sayings and references to honor. His speech is direct and undiplomatic, particularly when discussing political matters or expressing his views on non-Nords.', '* Drive the Imperial Legion from Haafingar and capture Solitude for the Stormcloak cause * Eliminate Thalmor influence from Skyrim entirely * Help establish Ulfric Stormcloak as the true High King * Restore traditional Nord values and governance to Skyrim * Create a pure Nordic society free from outside influence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('itinerant_lumberjack', 'A solitary Nord woodcutter who has taken up temporary residence in Morthal, notable for his irritable demeanor and preference for isolation. Despite his mundane occupation, his presence during Dark Brotherhood contracts suggests a darker significance to his role in Skyrim''s underworld, whether as a target or perhaps an unwitting pawn in larger schemes.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally from Kynesgrove, the lumberjack relocated to Morthal under mysterious circumstances, possibly fleeing from past troubles or seeking anonymity in the isolated marsh town. His defensive nature and choice to work at odd hours suggests a man either running from something or someone from his past.', 'Deeply private and irritable, showing clear disdain for social interaction and preferring to work alone. His aggressive responses to simple greetings hint at paranoia or past trauma that has left him distrustful of others, while his choice to work in exposed locations despite claiming to value privacy suggests internal contradiction.', 'A weathered Nord of typical robust build, with the muscular frame common to those who spend their days wielding axes. His hands are calloused from years of woodcutting, and his face bears the harsh lines of someone who spends long hours working outdoors in Skyrim''s unforgiving climate.', '* Jorgen and Lami - Neighbors, though he maintains minimal contact * Morthal Guards - Tense relationship due to his suspicious behavior * Local Woodcutters - Professional rivals or possible former colleagues * Dark Brotherhood - Potential target, suggesting possible unknown enemies', 'Works as an independent lumberjack, choosing to remain unaffiliated with local mills or logging operations. His ''itinerant'' nature suggests he takes temporary contracts or moves between settlements rather than maintaining stable employment.', '* Proficient with woodcutting axes for both logging and potential self-defense * Experienced in woodland navigation and survival * Basic weapon maintenance and sharpening abilities * Physical strength and endurance from years of manual labor', 'Speaks in short, irritated bursts with a harsh Nord accent, often using dismissive or hostile tones. His vocabulary is simple but direct, reflecting his practical occupation and desire to avoid lengthy interactions.', '* Maintain his privacy and avoid drawing attention from unknown pursuers * Earn enough septims to eventually move on to another hold * Possibly seeking revenge or resolution for past grievances * Survive despite being marked as a potential Dark Brotherhood target');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('j''darr', 'J''darr is a tragic figure found in the Alftand Glacial Ruins, a Khajiit whose severe skooma addiction and subsequent withdrawal transformed him from an expedition member into a delusional, violent shell of his former self. His deteriorating mental state, exacerbated by isolation and hunger in the ruins, leads to paranoid hallucinations and ultimately violent confrontations with anyone he encounters.', 'khajiit, thief', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Originally from an unknown region, J''darr developed a debilitating skooma addiction that severely impacted his life and relationships. His brother J''zhar, hoping to help him recover, enrolled them both in an expedition to explore Alftand, seeing it as an opportunity to force J''darr''s sobriety in an isolated environment. When their expedition became stranded and the skooma supplies ran out, J''darr''s withdrawal symptoms, combined with the harsh conditions and isolation, led to a complete mental breakdown.', 'Pre-addiction, J''darr likely possessed typical Khajiit traits of cunning and adaptability, though these were eroded by his dependency on skooma. In his current state, he is paranoid, delusional, and violent, unable to distinguish reality from hallucination. His personality is dominated by desperate cravings for skooma and increasing paranoia, leading him to suspect everyone of hiding his drug supply.', 'J''darr has the typical feline features of a Khajiit, though his physical condition has deteriorated due to withdrawal and malnutrition. His fur is likely matted and unkempt from his time in the ruins, and his eyes show the wild, unfocused look of someone in the grips of severe withdrawal.', '* J''zhar - Brother who tried to help him overcome his addiction, now deceased * Expedition Members - Former companions who abandoned the brothers after Dwarven automaton attacks * Umana - Fellow expedition member, relationship likely strained due to his condition * Sulla Trebatius - Expedition leader who abandoned him and his brother', 'J''darr was initially part of an expedition team exploring Alftand, though his role was likely minimal and arranged by his brother as rehabilitation. His current ''occupation'' consists solely of surviving in the ruins while searching desperately for skooma, having devolved into a hostile bandit-like existence.', '* Survival abilities allowing him to persist in harsh conditions * Natural Khajiit agility and night-vision capabilities * Basic combat skills with improvised weapons * Possible pre-addiction skills in stealth and theft, common among Khajiit', 'J''darr''s speech is fragmented and erratic, characterized by paranoid accusations and desperate pleas about skooma. He frequently talks to his dead brother, showing his disconnection from reality.', '* Find more skooma to satisfy his overwhelming addiction * Survive in the hostile environment of Alftand * Confront those he believes are hiding his skooma supply');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('j''datharr', 'J''datharr is a ruthless Khajiit assassin who serves as a covert operative for the Thalmor, masquerading as a merchant while carrying out targeted eliminations. His presence at the Windhelm caravan marks him as a deadly professional who combines traditional Khajiit stealth with Thalmor tactical precision.', 'khajiit, thief', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Recruited by the Thalmor for his natural Khajiit stealth abilities and lack of moral constraints, J''datharr built his reputation through successful eliminations of high-profile targets across Tamriel. His willingness to betray fellow Khajiit and work for the traditionally racist Thalmor suggests either a troubled past or deeply pragmatic worldview that prioritizes power and profit over cultural loyalty.', 'Cold, calculating, and utterly devoted to his Thalmor masters, J''datharr exhibits a predatory patience in stalking his targets. His threatening demeanor and menacing speech patterns reveal a sadistic enjoyment of his work, while his ability to maintain a merchant cover demonstrates sophisticated acting abilities and emotional control.', 'J''datharr possesses the typical feline features of a Khajiit, with sleek fur and sharp claws that serve him well in his assassination work. His movements are graceful yet purposeful, and his eyes hold the calculating gaze of a practiced killer.', '* Thalmor - Loyal employers who value his lethal effectiveness * Malborn - Current target marked for elimination * Khajiit Caravans - Maintains distance despite racial kinship * Ri''saad - Suspicious of his presence but tolerates it * Fellow Thalmor Agents - Professional cooperation only', 'J''datharr serves as a covert assassin for the Thalmor, using a merchant cover to move freely through Skyrim while eliminating designated targets. His position requires maintaining a delicate balance between appearing as a common trader while gathering intelligence and executing precision kills.', '* Master of stealth and silent elimination techniques * Expert in poisons and their tactical application * Proficient with both bow and blade for versatile killing options * Skilled in maintaining cover identities and gathering intelligence * Advanced knowledge of Thalmor operational procedures', 'J''datharr speaks in the traditional third-person Khajiit manner but with a cold, threatening undertone that betrays his true nature. His words are carefully chosen and often carry veiled threats, demonstrating both his Khajiit heritage and Thalmor training.', '* Successfully eliminate Malborn and other Thalmor targets * Maintain his valuable position within the Thalmor hierarchy * Advance the Thalmor agenda through covert operations * Perfect his assassination techniques and expand his methods');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('j''kier', 'J''Kier is a skilled Khajiit hunter and devout follower of Hircine who meets his end in Bloated Man''s Grotto while pursuing the werewolf Sinding. Despite his fatal wounds, he remains dedicated to the hunt until his final breath, embodying the unwavering spirit of a true hunter blessed by the Daedric Prince of the Hunt.', 'khajiit, warrior, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malehajiit', '', 'Born into one of Elsweyr''s nomadic trading caravans, J''Kier discovered his calling as a hunter at an early age while protecting the caravans from predators. His exceptional tracking abilities and fierce dedication eventually caught the attention of Hircine''s followers, leading him to abandon the merchant''s life for that of a devoted hunter. After years of proving himself in increasingly dangerous hunts across Tamriel, he earned the right to participate in Hircine''s Great Hunt.', 'J''Kier is characterized by his unwavering dedication to the hunt and deep religious devotion to Hircine. Even in the face of death, he maintains his focus on the sacred nature of the hunt, showing both stoic acceptance of his fate and fierce determination. His reverence for hunting traditions and respect for worthy prey suggests a complex warrior code that governs his actions.', 'J''Kier possesses the typical lithe but muscular build of a Khajiit hunter, with sleek fur bearing the distinctive striped patterns of his race. Battle scars across his body tell the tale of countless hunts, while his sharp claws and keen eyes mark him as a natural predator.', '* Lord Hircine - Revered deity and master whom he serves with unwavering devotion * Fellow Hunters - Brothers and sisters in the Great Hunt, united in purpose * Sinding - Respected but condemned prey whose strength proved greater than anticipated * Hunting Groups - Various connections with hunter organizations across Skyrim', 'J''Kier serves as a dedicated hunter in service to Lord Hircine, participating in sacred hunts and tracking worthy prey across Tamriel. His position as a chosen hunter in Hircine''s Great Hunt marks him as an elite among his peers, trusted with pursuing the most dangerous and significant quarry.', '* Expert tracker capable of pursuing prey across any terrain * Accomplished swordsman combining Khajiit agility with Nordic hunting techniques * Skilled in survival and wilderness navigation * Natural night vision and enhanced senses typical of Khajiit hunters * Intimate knowledge of hunting rituals and Hircine''s teachings', 'J''Kier speaks with the traditional Khajiit third-person manner, though his speech patterns are more direct and fierce than typical merchant Khajiit. His tone carries the gravity and conviction of a religious warrior, speaking with reverence about the hunt and Hircine.', '* Successfully complete Hircine''s Great Hunt by bringing down Sinding * Prove himself worthy of Hircine''s continued favor through dedication to the hunt * Achieve glory and honor through pursuing the most challenging and dangerous prey * Pass on the sacred traditions of the hunt to worthy successors');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('j''zargo', 'J''zargo is an ambitious and prideful Khajiit mage studying as an apprentice at the College of Winterhold. Known for his exceptional confidence and competitive nature, he masks a genuine dedication to magical mastery beneath his arrogant exterior, while his uncapped magical potential hints at greater capabilities than his fellow students.', 'khajiit, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born into one of Elsweyr''s Khajiiti tribes, J''zargo demonstrated magical aptitude from an early age. Seeking to prove himself among the greatest mages in Tamriel, he made the long journey to Skyrim and gained admission to the College of Winterhold, where his natural talents and fierce determination have made him a notable, if sometimes controversial, apprentice.', 'J''zargo is defined by his overwhelming confidence and competitive drive, often bordering on arrogance. While he can be manipulative and potentially dangerous in his ambition, he maintains a code of honor and shows genuine respect to those who prove themselves his equals or betters. His boastful nature masks a deep insecurity about proving himself in a land traditionally suspicious of both Khajiit and magic users.', 'J''zargo has the typical feline features of a Khajiit, with distinctive grey-white fur and alert, intelligent eyes. His physique is lean and agile, typical of his race, though he carries himself with the careful poise of a practiced mage rather than the predatory grace common to many Khajiit.', '* College of Winterhold Faculty - Respectful but ambitious student seeking to prove his superiority * Tolfdir - Primary instructor whom he generally respects despite his competitive nature * Fellow Apprentices - Views them as rivals, particularly in magical studies * Dragonborn - Initially a competitor, potentially becoming a respected ally * The Blades - Possible future allegiance if recruited', 'J''zargo serves as an apprentice mage at the College of Winterhold, focusing primarily on mastering Destruction magic while pursuing knowledge in all schools of magic. His position involves both studying existing magical theories and conducting his own experimental research, sometimes with dangerous results.', '* Master of Destruction magic with particular expertise in shock spells * Competent in all schools of magic including ward-casting * Natural aptitude for magical experimentation and research * Skilled magical combatant with unlimited potential for growth * Traditional Khajiiti stealth abilities, though rarely employed', 'J''zargo speaks in third person, referring to himself by name, with the typical Khajiiti accent and speech patterns. His tone is usually confident and slightly condescending, often incorporating boasts about his magical prowess or potential.', '* Become the most powerful mage in the College of Winterhold * Master all schools of magic, particularly Destruction * Prove that Khajiit can excel in magical studies despite Nordic prejudices * Discover or create new and powerful spells * Achieve recognition as one of the greatest mages in Tamriel');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('j''zhar', 'J''zhar was a Khajiit witchblade who met his tragic end in the Alftand Glacial Ruins while exploring Dwemer ruins with his brother J''darr. A skilled practitioner of both magic and blade arts, his final days were marked by the desperate struggle to survive against both Dwemer automatons and his brother''s growing skooma-induced madness.', 'khajiit, thief, pale', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born into a Khajiit trading family, J''zhar developed an early fascination with both combat and magic, eventually becoming a witchblade. He and his brother J''darr traveled to Skyrim seeking adventure and knowledge in Dwemer ruins, though their expedition to Alftand would prove fatal. Their final expedition was marked by dwindling supplies, Dwemer automaton attacks, and his brother''s deteriorating mental state due to skooma withdrawal.', 'J''zhar was methodical and scholarly, maintaining detailed research notes even in dire circumstances. His journal entries reveal a protective and patient nature, particularly in dealing with his brother''s addiction. Despite facing death, he remained analytical and composed, documenting their circumstances until the end.', 'Like most Khajiit, J''zhar possessed the characteristic feline features of his race, with fur-covered body and a tail. His time in the harsh climate of Skyrim and the dangerous expedition had left him lean and weather-worn, though his body retained the muscular definition common to those who practice both magic and martial combat.', '* J''darr - Younger brother and traveling companion, whose skooma addiction ultimately led to J''zhar''s death * College of Winterhold - Possible former associate, given his faction alignment * Fellow Explorers - Maintained distance from other expedition members in Alftand', 'J''zhar served as both a scholar and explorer, combining his combat abilities with academic pursuit of Dwemer knowledge. His role as a witchblade allowed him to protect himself and his brother while documenting their discoveries in the dangerous ruins they explored.', '* Proficient in both destruction magic and one-handed weapons as a witchblade * Experienced in academic research and documentation * Survival skills necessary for extended expeditions * Knowledge of Dwemer ruins and artifacts', 'Based on his journal entries, J''zhar spoke with an educated vocabulary while maintaining the traditional Khajiit speech pattern of referring to himself in third person. His writing reveals a precise and analytical mind in how he documented events.', '* Document and understand Dwemer technology and architecture * Help his brother overcome skooma addiction * Survive the dangerous expedition through Alftand * Advance his knowledge and practice as a witchblade');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jala', 'Jala is a resilient Nord merchant who runs a successful produce stand in Solitude''s marketplace, having persevered through personal tragedy and wartime hardships. She maintains one of the most reliable sources of fresh fruit and vegetables in the city, while carrying the emotional burden of her brother''s death at the hands of Stormcloaks.', 'nord, merchant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Originally from Whiterun Hold, Jala relocated to Solitude after her brother was killed by Stormcloaks, seeking a fresh start in the Imperial-controlled capital. She established herself as a merchant by developing reliable trade connections with seafaring vessels, though her business has faced challenges from pirates like the Blackblood Marauders.', 'Jala is an industrious and sociable merchant who maintains a cheerful facade despite harboring deep grief and anger over her brother''s death. She demonstrates remarkable resilience in maintaining her business through difficult times, while her chatty nature and knowledge of local gossip makes her a valuable source of information about Solitude''s happenings.', 'A hardy Nord woman with the weathered features typical of someone who works long hours outdoors in Skyrim''s harsh climate. She maintains a neat, practical appearance suitable for a merchant who deals with the public daily.', '* Evette San - Fellow merchant and friend in the Solitude marketplace * Addvar - Neighboring fish vendor and business associate * Jaree-Ra - Suspicious Argonian who occasionally visits her stand * Captain Aldis - Regular customer from the Solitude guard * Deceased Brother - Killed by Stormcloaks in Whiterun, driving her deep antipathy toward the rebellion', 'Jala owns and operates a produce stand in Solitude''s marketplace, working long hours to provide fresh fruits and vegetables to the city''s residents. She maintains trade relationships with shipping merchants to ensure a steady supply of fresh goods, despite the challenges posed by pirates and the civil war.', '* Expert haggling and mercantile abilities * Knowledge of produce quality and preservation * Basic self-defense with an iron dagger * Skilled at gathering and managing information through customer interactions * Experienced in maintaining trade relationships with suppliers', 'Jala speaks in a direct, friendly manner typical of marketplace vendors, often using her wares as conversation starters. Her speech carries undertones of both cheerful merchant banter and world-weary pragmatism, occasionally revealing her deep-seated anger toward the Stormcloaks.', '* Maintain a successful business despite the challenges of war and piracy * See justice served to the Stormcloaks for her brother''s death * Expand her trade connections to ensure more reliable produce shipments * Establish herself as one of Solitude''s most respected merchants');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('japhet', 'Japhet was a determined Nordic settler who attempted to establish a fortress on a remote island near Windhelm, only to meet a tragic end and become a draugr. His tale exemplifies both the pioneering spirit of Nordic settlers and the harsh realities of Skyrim''s unforgiving wilderness.', 'nord', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born to farming parents near Dawnstar, Japhet dreamed of establishing his own settlement and legacy. He gathered a small group of followers and attempted to build a fortress on an isolated island, but the harsh conditions and limited resources led to his followers abandoning the project. In his final days, he survived by eating ice moss until succumbing to the elements, later rising as a draugr due to his strong will and refusal to abandon his dream.', 'Japhet exhibited exceptional determination and stubbornness, refusing to abandon his vision even when faced with overwhelming odds. His journal entries reveal a proud and independent spirit, though his unwavering dedication to his goals ultimately bordered on destructive obsession. Despite setbacks, he maintained an almost delusional optimism about his fortress''s potential.', 'As a draugr, Japhet retains the desiccated form of a Nordic male, with withered gray skin stretched tight over his skeletal frame. His body shows signs of the harsh conditions he endured, including frost damage and malnutrition from his final days surviving on ice moss.', '* Unnamed Followers - Former companions who abandoned his fortress project * Father - Unknown farmer who likely influenced his agricultural knowledge * Dawnstar Citizens - Former neighbors who likely thought him foolish for his ambitious plans * Local Spirits - The ghosts he believed haunted the island in his final days', 'Originally a farmer''s son, Japhet became a would-be settlement founder and fortress builder. His attempt to establish a settlement showcases the entrepreneurial spirit common among Nordic pioneers, though his project ultimately failed.', '* Agricultural knowledge from his farming background * Basic construction and fortification building capabilities * Survival skills, particularly in harsh coastal environments * Leadership abilities, though ultimately insufficient to maintain follower loyalty', 'His written accounts demonstrate a formal and determined tone, with a tendency toward stubborn optimism even in dire circumstances. His language reflects his farming background while maintaining a sense of authority and vision.', '* Complete the construction of his fortress and establish a lasting settlement * Prove his worth as a leader and settlement founder * Create a legacy that would survive beyond his lifetime * Demonstrate the viability of his chosen island location');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jaree-ra', 'Jaree-Ra is a cunning Argonian criminal who maintains a facade of legitimate employment while orchestrating maritime theft operations in Solitude. As the leader of a sophisticated smuggling operation working with the Blackblood Marauders, he uses his position at the East Empire Company as cover for more nefarious activities.', 'argonian, thief, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Born into a family of criminals, Jaree-Ra grew up learning the arts of deception and theft alongside his siblings Deeja and Gulum-Ei. He established himself in Solitude, carefully building a network of contacts and criminal connections while maintaining a legitimate front as a dockworker, eventually forming an alliance with the notorious Blackblood Marauders.', 'Jaree-Ra is manipulative and opportunistic, skilled at presenting a trustworthy facade while harboring darker intentions. He shows little remorse for his actions, viewing theft and deception as natural means of advancement, and demonstrates particular cunning in how he uses his legitimate employment to facilitate his criminal enterprises.', 'A tall, well-built Argonian with dark green scales and amber eyes typical of his race. His physical appearance reflects his dual life - muscular enough to be believable as a dockworker, yet agile and dexterous as befits a career criminal.', '* Deeja - Sister and trusted criminal partner in their smuggling operations * Gulum-Ei - Brother who serves as a fence for the Thieves Guild * Vittoria Vici - Employer at the East Empire Company, unaware of his true nature * Blackblood Marauders - Criminal associates in various theft operations * Angeline Morrard - Landlord who provides him lodging, likely unaware of his criminal activities', 'Jaree-Ra maintains a cover job as a dockworker at the East Empire Company while secretly operating as a criminal mastermind. He coordinates with the Blackblood Marauders to orchestrate ship robberies and smuggling operations, using his legitimate position to gather intelligence on potential targets.', '* Expert in maritime navigation and shipping operations * Skilled in deception and maintaining false identities * Proficient in light combat and stealth techniques * Advanced knowledge of smuggling routes and cargo vessel operations * Natural leadership abilities in coordinating criminal operations', 'Speaks in a smooth, persuasive manner with the distinct Argonian accent, often using subtle manipulation and suggestion. His vocabulary alternates between common dockworker parlance and more sophisticated language when dealing with potential marks.', '* Expand his criminal enterprise beyond Solitude''s borders * Maintain his cover as a legitimate dockworker while growing his illegal operations * Accumulate wealth through increasingly ambitious maritime heists * Strengthen his alliance with the Blackblood Marauders for mutual profit');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jawanan', 'Jawanan is a dedicated Redguard fletcher apprentice who left his homeland of Hammerfell to study under the master craftsman Fihada in Solitude. Despite his technical skill with bow-making, he is a somewhat socially awkward individual who dreams of exploring Skyrim''s wonders while honing his craft.', 'redguard, archer, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Jawanan was drawn to Skyrim by tales of Fihada''s legendary fletching abilities. He made the long journey to Solitude specifically to apprentice under the former Imperial ranger, leaving behind his homeland to pursue his passion for bow-making. While his early life remains largely unknown, his deep knowledge of fletching suggests he likely had prior training or experience in Hammerfell.', 'Jawanan is earnest and eager to please, though he openly acknowledges his lack of social grace. He demonstrates a curious and adventurous spirit, often expressing wonder at Skyrim''s legendary locations and natural phenomena. Despite his social awkwardness, particularly evident in his failed attempts at romance, he maintains a positive and hardworking attitude focused on mastering his craft.', 'As a Redguard, Jawanan has dark skin and strong, athletic features typical of his race. He appears to be in his early to mid-twenties, with a craftsman''s capable hands and the proper posture required for precise fletching work.', '* Fihada - Respected master and mentor in the art of fletching * Vivienne Onis - Object of failed romantic interest who rejected his advances * Erdi - More receptive to his attempts at friendship and conversation * Local Solitude residents - Maintains cordial but somewhat awkward relations with townspeople', 'Jawanan serves as the apprentice fletcher at Solitude''s Fletcher shop, learning the craft of bow and arrow making under Fihada''s tutelage. He assists with daily operations of the shop and takes over as the primary vendor should anything happen to his master.', '* Expert fletching and bow-making abilities * Detailed knowledge of archery equipment and maintenance * Basic business and merchant skills * Fundamental understanding of wood properties and arrow dynamics', 'Jawanan speaks with formal politeness, frequently using respectful terms like ''sir'' and showing deference to his master. His speech patterns reveal both his foreign origins and his enthusiasm for sharing knowledge about fletching and Skyrim''s wonders, though he often stumbles in casual social conversation.', '* Master the art of fletching under Fihada''s guidance * Explore Skyrim''s wonders, particularly Windhelm and Volskygge * Improve his social skills and perhaps find romance * Eventually establish himself as a respected fletcher in his own right');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jayri', 'Jayri is a displaced Redguard refugee seeking sanctuary from the growing vampire menace that threatens Skyrim''s settlements. Despite being denied entry to Fort Dawnguard, she persists in staying within Dayspring Canyon, emblematic of the civilian population''s struggle against supernatural threats during the vampire crisis.', 'redguard, peasant, rift, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Originally from a small settlement in Skyrim, Jayri lived a peaceful life as a farmer until vampire attacks forced her to flee her home. After witnessing horrific nighttime raids on nearby villages and possibly losing family members to the vampire menace, she made the desperate journey to Fort Dawnguard seeking protection, only to find herself among other refugees denied entry to the fortress.', 'Jayri exhibits a combination of persistent determination and perpetual anxiety, refusing to leave the relative safety of Dayspring Canyon despite being denied fortress access. Her demeanor reflects both resilience in the face of adversity and deep-seated trauma from her experiences with vampire attacks, manifesting in her sleepless vigilance and constant state of worry.', 'A Redguard woman of average height with the characteristic dark skin and athletic build common to her race. Her face shows signs of stress and sleeplessness, with dark circles under her eyes and worry lines etched into her features.', '* Fort Dawnguard Guards - Tense relationship due to being denied entry to the fortress * Fellow Refugees - Shares common cause and mutual support with others seeking protection * Vampire Victims - Likely lost family members or neighbors to vampire attacks * Local Settlements - Former connections to farming communities now threatened by vampires', 'Formerly a farmer who has been displaced by vampire attacks, Jayri now exists as a refugee in Dayspring Canyon. She contributes to the refugee camp by performing basic tasks like chopping wood and cooking, though these activities seem more about maintaining sanity than true productivity.', '* Basic farming and agricultural knowledge * Survival skills developed from fleeing vampire attacks * Cooking and food preparation abilities * Wood chopping and basic camp maintenance', 'Speaks with a worried and pleading tone, her voice often trembling with fear and desperation. Her manner of speech reflects her constant state of anxiety, frequently expressing concerns about safety and the future.', '* Find permanent safe shelter from vampire attacks * Eventually return home once the vampire crisis is resolved * Survive the current vampire threat plaguing Skyrim * Protect herself and fellow refugees from supernatural dangers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jenassa', 'Jenassa is a skilled Dunmer ranger and mercenary who combines lethal combat prowess with an artist''s appreciation for the deadly craft of battle. She views herself as a creator of deadly art, using blade and shadow to paint in strokes of blood, while maintaining a pragmatic approach to earning her living through her martial talents.', 'darkelf, archer, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Jenassa left her homeland to seek fortune as a sellsword in Skyrim. She initially considered banditry but chose instead to pursue legitimate mercenary work, eventually settling in Whiterun where her reputation for reliability and skill has earned her a steady stream of clients.', 'Jenassa is confident, direct, and takes pride in her lethal abilities, viewing combat as an art form rather than mere violence. She maintains a professional demeanor with clients while displaying a poetic appreciation for her deadly craft. Though capable of working alone, she values loyalty to her patrons and executes her duties with unwavering dedication.', 'A typical Dunmer with ashen gray skin and the characteristic red eyes of her race. Her lean, athletic build reflects her life as a ranger and warrior, while her movements display the fluid grace of one accustomed to stealth and precision combat.', '* Elrindir - Business association with the owner of Drunken Huntsman who allows her to seek clients there * Whiterun Guards - Professional respect as a legitimate mercenary rather than a common sellsword * Various Merchants - Maintains good standing with local traders for equipment and supplies * Potential Spouse - Can develop a romantic relationship with her employer', 'Jenassa works as a professional mercenary and ranger-for-hire, operating primarily out of the Drunken Huntsman in Whiterun. She offers her services to paying clients, specializing in wilderness navigation, combat support, and protection duties.', '* Expert archer with exceptional accuracy and tactical awareness * Skilled dual-wielding warrior capable of deadly close-quarters combat * Master of stealth and shadowy approaches * Wilderness survival and tracking expertise * Proficient in light armor and mobility-focused combat', 'Jenassa speaks with a sophisticated vocabulary that often frames violence in artistic terms, referring to death as her ''art'' and combat as her ''craft.'' Her tone is confident and professional, with occasional poetic flourishes that reflect her unique perspective on battle.', '* Build a reputation as one of Skyrim''s most skilled and reliable mercenaries * Perfect her deadly ''art'' through challenging combat encounters * Accumulate wealth and status through her mercenary work * Find a worthy long-term patron who can appreciate her artistic approach to warfare');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jervar', 'Jervar is a young Nord stablehand working at Whiterun Stables under his critical and demanding father Skulvar. Despite his dedication to the family business, he harbors secret dreams of adventure and dragon-slaying, creating a constant internal conflict between duty and desire.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun, Jervar has spent his entire life working at the family stables, learning the trade from his father Skulvar. His mother''s absence (presumably deceased) has left him solely under his father''s stern guidance, leading to a strained relationship marked by constant criticism and doubt. His upbringing has been defined by hard physical labor and the expectation that he will eventually inherit and manage the stables.', 'Jervar is a hardworking but frustrated young man who feels trapped by his circumstances and his father''s constant belittlement. He shows signs of a dreamer''s spirit, fantasizing about dragon-hunting adventures while maintaining a pragmatic work ethic. Though competent at his job, his heart isn''t in the stable work, leading to a complex mix of responsibility and resentment.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of someone who performs daily physical labor. His hands are calloused from years of stable work, and his face shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors year-round.', '* Skulvar Sable-Hilt - Father and employer, relationship marked by tension and criticism * Lillith Maiden-Loom - Technical owner of the stables, maintains a distant business relationship * Local Guards - Casual acquaintances who frequently pass by the stables * Whiterun merchants - Professional connections through the stables business', 'Jervar works as a stablehand at Whiterun Stables, performing various duties including horse grooming, shoeing, mucking stalls, and general maintenance. He serves as his father''s assistant and heir apparent to the stable management, though his father questions his capability for the role.', '* Basic horse care and maintenance including grooming, shoeing, and feeding * Rudimentary weapon handling with an iron dagger * Physical strength and endurance from years of manual labor * Basic business knowledge gained from working at the stables', 'Jervar speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner that often carries undertones of frustration or resentment. His speech patterns reflect his working-class background, using simple language and occasionally showing defiance when addressing his father.', '* Prove himself capable of running the stables despite his father''s doubts * Break free from the family business to pursue adventures and dragon hunting * Earn enough money to potentially start his own venture * Gain recognition and respect independent of his father''s influence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jesper', 'Jesper is a dedicated Nord miner at Rockwallow Mine who embodies the Nordic values of hard work and purposeful living. He represents the working class of Skyrim, finding meaning and contentment in the simple but demanding life of a miner while maintaining a strong desire to avoid complications or trouble.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born into the harsh climate of Skyrim, Jesper likely came from a working-class family that instilled in him the value of honest labor. He found his calling in the mining trade, eventually settling in Stonehills where the steady work and simple lifestyle aligned with his values. His choice to live in a camp rather than seek more comfortable accommodations suggests either a humble upbringing or a conscious choice to live modestly.', 'Jesper is an industrious and focused individual who values routine and stability above all else. He shows little interest in matters beyond his work, displaying a pragmatic and somewhat isolationist attitude toward life. His responses to others are typically brief and work-focused, suggesting someone who finds security in maintaining clear boundaries and a structured existence.', 'As a Nord miner, Jesper likely possesses the sturdy build typical of his race, with well-developed muscles from years of physical labor. His hands would be calloused from continuous mining work, and his skin weather-beaten from exposure to Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Gestur Rockbreaker - His supervisor, whom he treats with clear respect and deference * Fellow Miners - Maintains cordial but primarily professional relationships with coworkers * Stonehills Community - Part of the tight-knit mining settlement, though keeps mostly to himself', 'Jesper works as a full-time miner at Rockwallow Mine, following a strict daily schedule of mining, meals, and wood chopping. His position requires physical endurance and technical knowledge of mining operations, working under Gestur Rockbreaker''s supervision to extract valuable ore from the mine.', '* Experienced in mining techniques and ore extraction * Proficient with mining tools and equipment * Capable woodcutter during off-hours * Basic self-defense abilities with an iron dagger * Physical endurance and strength from daily labor', 'Jesper speaks in short, direct sentences, often emphasizing his desire to focus on work and avoid trouble. His tone is respectful but distant, particularly when addressing his supervisor.', '* Maintain his stable position at Rockwallow Mine * Continue earning a honest living through his mining work * Avoid complications or trouble that might disrupt his simple lifestyle * Potentially save enough money to improve his living conditions, though content with current situation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jiub', 'Jiub is a legendary Dark Elf scout turned saint who achieved fame by eradicating the dreaded Cliff Racers from Vvardenfell, earning him the grand title ''Saint Jiub the Eradicator of the Winged Menace.'' Now trapped in the Soul Cairn after being soul trapped during the Oblivion Crisis, he continues his life''s work as an author, searching for the scattered pages of his multi-volume autobiography.', 'darkelf, scholar, soulcairn', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally a humble scout in Morrowind, Jiub gained prominence through his successful campaign to rid Vvardenfell of the notorious Cliff Racers, a task that earned him sainthood. His life came to an tragic end during the Oblivion Crisis when he was soul trapped by a Dremora during the siege of Kvatch, leading to his current existence in the Soul Cairn. Though he died around 3E 433, he remains unaware that over two centuries have passed since his death.', 'Jiub exhibits a grandiose and somewhat pompous demeanor, frequently emphasizing his titles and achievements. He is passionate about his writing to the point of obsession, easily irritated by interruptions, and maintains an air of self-importance despite his circumstances. Despite his eccentric nature, he shows remarkable dedication to his work and maintains an unwavering focus on completing his opus.', 'As a Dark Elf, Jiub has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race. His face bears the weathered features of one who spent years in the harsh conditions of Vvardenfell, with distinctive scarring across his right eye. His physical form in the Soul Cairn maintains the appearance he had at the time of his death, though with an ethereal quality common to souls trapped in this realm.', '* Cliff Racers - Former nemeses whom he successfully eradicated from Vvardenfell * The Tribunal Temple - Recognized his achievements by granting him sainthood * Dremora - Responsible for his death and soul trapping during the Oblivion Crisis * Soul Cairn Inhabitants - Fellow trapped souls whom he largely avoids to focus on his writing', 'In life, Jiub served as a scout in Morrowind before becoming famous as the eradicator of Cliff Racers. In death, he has taken up the role of an author, dedicating himself to completing his 26-volume autobiography chronicling his life''s achievements.', '* Expert scout with extensive knowledge of Vvardenfell''s terrain * Masterful hunter specialized in tracking and eliminating Cliff Racers * Accomplished writer with a flair for dramatic narrative * Proficient with daggers and light armor * Survival expert with experience in harsh environments', 'Jiub speaks with a formal, often grandiose manner, frequently referring to himself in the third person and using his full title. His vocabulary is elaborate and theatrical, befitting his self-image as both a saint and an accomplished author.', '* Complete his 26-volume opus detailing his life''s achievements * Recover all lost pages of his writings scattered throughout the Soul Cairn * Ensure his legacy as Saint Jiub the Eradicator is remembered in Tamriel * Find a way to have his completed works published and distributed in the mortal realm');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jod', 'Jod is the steadfast and dutiful captain of the guard in Dawnstar who serves as housecarl to Jarl Skald. A veteran of the Great War against the Thalmor, he prioritizes the safety and protection of Dawnstar''s citizens over political allegiances, often acting as a voice of reason to temper Skald''s militant anti-Imperial stance.', 'nord, guard, noble, pale', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Jod earned his position through distinguished service in the Great War against the Thalmor, where he witnessed firsthand the courage of Imperial Legionnaires. His experiences in war shaped his pragmatic approach to leadership and protection, leading him to value peace and security over ideological conflicts. After the war, he was appointed as Dawnstar''s guard captain and housecarl, roles he has maintained with unwavering dedication.', 'Level-headed and practical, Jod demonstrates a measured approach to his duties that contrasts with Jarl Skald''s passionate anti-Imperial rhetoric. He shows genuine concern for the citizens'' welfare and maintains a professional demeanor even in tense situations. Though loyal to Skald, he''s not afraid to voice dissenting opinions when citizens'' safety is at stake.', 'A weathered Nord warrior with the bearing of a veteran soldier, Jod''s physical presence commands respect without being overtly intimidating. His body bears the scars of his military service, and his stance reflects years of combat training and guard duty. He maintains the fit physique required of an active guard captain.', '* Jarl Skald - Serves as his housecarl, though often disagrees with his aggressive stance toward the Empire * Dawnstar Guard Force - Commands and trains the local guards with respected authority * Citizens of Dawnstar - Maintains protective, professional relationships with the townspeople * Imperial Legion - Holds respect for their fighting capabilities despite current political tensions', 'As captain of the guard and housecarl to Jarl Skald, Jod oversees Dawnstar''s security forces and serves as the Jarl''s personal protector. He manages guard rotations, maintains order in the city, and provides military counsel to the Jarl, though his advice often emphasizes caution over aggression.', '* Veteran warrior with extensive combat experience from the Great War * Skilled commander and tactician in charge of city defense * Proficient with traditional Nord weapons, particularly the war axe and shield * Expert in guard deployment and city security protocols * Diplomatic abilities in managing relations between citizens and authority', 'Speaks with the direct, no-nonsense tone of a military commander, but maintains a respectful and diplomatic manner. His word choice reflects his practical nature and years of command experience.', '* Maintain peace and security in Dawnstar despite political tensions * Protect citizens from both external threats and the consequences of war * Balance loyalty to Jarl Skald with practical protection of Dawnstar''s interests * Preserve order and stability regardless of which side controls the city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jofthor', 'Jofthor is a hardworking Nord farmer and protective father who runs Fellstar Farm in the small town of Ivarstead. He represents the traditional values of rural Skyrim life while struggling with the changing times and his daughter''s desires to leave home, embodying the tension between preserving community traditions and accepting inevitable change.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Ivarstead, Jofthor inherited Fellstar Farm from his parents and has worked the land his entire life. He married Boti, who once shared similar dreams of adventure as their daughter, but chose to settle down and build a life in Ivarstead. The couple has witnessed their town''s gradual decline as younger residents leave for opportunities in larger cities, intensifying Jofthor''s protective nature toward his only child.', 'Jofthor is stern, traditional, and deeply protective of both his family and his way of life. While his exterior can be gruff and inflexible, particularly regarding his daughter''s choices, he harbors deep fears about losing his only child and seeing his community further diminish. Though sometimes overbearing, his actions stem from genuine love and concern rather than malice.', 'A sturdy Nord man of middle age, with the weathered features and strong build typical of someone who has spent their life working the land. His hands are calloused from years of farming, and his face shows the lines of both worry and exposure to the elements.', '* Boti - His wife who often mediates between him and their daughter * Fastred - His beloved but rebellious teenage daughter * Bassianus Axius - Potential suitor of his daughter whom he disapproves of * Klimmek - Former love interest of his daughter whom he viewed more favorably * Wilhelm - Local innkeeper who keeps him informed of his daughter''s activities', 'Jofthor owns and operates Fellstar Farm, one of the primary agricultural establishments in Ivarstead. His work involves maintaining the farm, managing crops, and contributing to the local food supply, making him an essential member of the small community.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of agriculture and crop management * Capable of operating and maintaining farming equipment and tools * Basic combat abilities with a dagger for self-defense * Knowledge of local geography and weather patterns', 'He speaks in a direct, often blunt manner typical of Nord farmers, frequently expressing his worries and frustrations openly. His tone can shift from gruff and stern when dealing with his daughter''s behavior to weary and concerned when discussing the future of Ivarstead.', '* Protect his daughter while keeping her close to home and safe from the dangers of the world * Maintain the viability of Fellstar Farm for future generations * Preserve the traditional way of life in Ivarstead despite the exodus of young people * Ensure his family''s security and prosperity in an increasingly uncertain world');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jon_battle-born', 'Jon Battle-Born is a thoughtful and artistic Nord who stands apart from the typical warrior culture of Skyrim, pursuing his passion for bardic traditions while caught between his family''s expectations and his secret love for Olfina Gray-Mane. Despite being born into one of Whiterun''s most prominent clans, he yearns to escape the bitter feud between the Battle-Borns and Gray-Manes to forge his own path as a bard.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, legion', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into the prestigious Battle-Born clan of Whiterun, Jon was raised amid wealth and political influence but developed an early appreciation for poetry and music rather than traditional Nordic warrior values. His upbringing during the growing tension between the Battle-Borns and Gray-Manes has shaped his perspective on the futility of ancient feuds, leading him to secretly rebel against his family''s expectations.', 'Jon is notably more laid-back and philosophical than the typical Nord, preferring poetry and song to violence and warfare. He shows remarkable independence of thought, rejecting his family''s feuds and the civil war''s black-and-white mentality. Despite his gentle nature, he possesses the courage to pursue a forbidden romance and stand by his convictions.', 'Jon is a young Nord man with the typical robust Nordic build, though perhaps slightly less muscular than most warrior-focused Nords. He has the characteristic fair complexion of his race and maintains a neat, clean-cut appearance befitting his artistic aspirations and merchant district upbringing.', '* Olfina Gray-Mane - Secret lover and confidante, sharing a forbidden romance across family lines * Battle-Born Clan - His immediate family, who disapprove of his bardic aspirations * Mikael - Fellow bard whom he disdains for his superficial approach to the craft * Gray-Mane Clan - Technical rivals due to family feud, though he personally rejects the conflict * Belethor - Frequent acquaintance due to spending time near his shop', 'Jon is officially a member of the Battle-Born clan''s merchant activities, though he spends most of his time pursuing his true passion as an aspiring bard. He splits his time between the Plains District during the day and performing at The Bannered Mare at night.', '* Trained in basic combat and swordsmanship as expected of Battle-Born clan members * Talented musician and poet with particular skill in Nordic bardic traditions * Competent public speaker and performer * Basic merchant skills from family business exposure', 'Jon speaks with a refined yet casual Nord accent, using more poetic and philosophical language than typical Nords. His speech often includes references to art, music, and life''s finer pleasures rather than the usual warrior rhetoric.', '* Gain admission to the Bards College in Solitude to pursue his true calling * Escape Whiterun''s clan feuds with Olfina and build a life focused on art and music * Help bring an end to the senseless conflict between the Battle-Borns and Gray-Manes * Prove that there''s more to Nordic culture than just fighting and death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jonna', 'Jonna is a resilient Redguard innkeeper who left her homeland of Hammerfell to establish a new life in Skyrim''s harsh marshlands. Running the struggling Moorside Inn in Morthal, she maintains a stoic determination despite the establishment''s lack of business, serving as one of the town''s few reliable sources of shelter and information for travelers.', 'redguard, innkeeper, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Jonna followed her brother Falion to Skyrim to escape the political turmoil in their homeland. She established herself in Morthal not by choice but by circumstance, taking on the role of innkeeper to give herself purpose while her brother pursued his magical studies. Despite the inn''s poor performance and the suspicious nature of local residents, she has persevered in maintaining the establishment.', 'Practical and direct, Jonna maintains a no-nonsense attitude that helps her cope with the challenges of running an unsuccessful business. While she can be gruff, she shows patience with paying customers and loyalty to her brother, though she''s protective of him against those who might harass him about his magical practices. Her resilience is evident in her ability to maintain optimism despite the inn''s constant lack of patronage.', 'A middle-aged Redguard woman with the characteristic dark skin and strong physical features of her race. Her years of hard work are evident in her weathered appearance and strong hands, though she maintains a dignified bearing despite the harsh conditions of Morthal.', '* Falion - Brother and closest family member, whom she followed to Morthal * Lurbuk - Tenant and occasional annoyance, though she tolerates him for the steady income * Morthal Residents - Generally neutral relationships, though somewhat distant * Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - Professional relationship as a business owner in her hold', 'Jonna serves as the owner and sole proprietor of the Moorside Inn in Morthal. Her duties include serving food and drink, renting rooms, maintaining the premises, and providing information to travelers about local events and opportunities. She works extremely long hours, apparently never sleeping, to keep the establishment running.', '* Experienced innkeeper with knowledge of food preparation and preservation * Capable of self-defense with an iron dagger * Administrative abilities in managing an establishment * Knowledge of local geography and dangers in the marsh * Basic mercantile skills for running a business', 'Jonna speaks with a distinctive informal dialect, dropping her ''g''s at the end of words and using contractions frequently. Her tone is direct and practical, often reflecting her resigned attitude toward her struggling business.', '* Maintain a viable business despite the lack of customers in Morthal * Support and protect her brother Falion from hostile locals * Eventually turn the Moorside Inn into a more profitable establishment * Create a stable life away from the troubles of Hammerfell');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jora', 'Jora is a devoted Nord priestess who maintains unwavering faith in Talos despite the Empire''s ban on his worship. She serves at the Temple of Talos in Windhelm alongside her husband, choosing to ignore the White-Gold Concordat while placing her trust in Ulfric Stormcloak''s protection against the Thalmor.', 'nord, priest, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Jora dedicated her life to the priesthood of Talos from an early age. She witnessed the signing of the White-Gold Concordat and its devastating impact on Talos worship, which only strengthened her resolve to maintain her faith. Her dedication led her to become one of the few remaining open priestesses of Talos in Skyrim, protected within Windhelm''s walls.', 'Jora is steadfast and practical in her devotion, maintaining a stoic demeanor even in the face of religious persecution. She exhibits quiet resilience and unwavering conviction in her beliefs, often using her faith as a source of comfort during troubled times. While generally composed, she harbors deep resentment toward the Thalmor and those who would suppress Talos worship.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the weathered features typical of her race, carrying herself with dignified bearing despite her advancing years. Her face shows the lines of someone who spends much time in contemplation and prayer, with clear eyes that reflect her inner conviction.', '* Lortheim - Her husband and fellow priest, though their marriage shows signs of strain * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respected protector of the temple and champion of Talos worship * Hillevi Cruel-Sea - Regular temple visitor and confidante * Shatter-Shield Family - Frequent visitors seeking solace after their loss * Captain Lonely-Gale - Occasional visitor to the temple * Thalmor - Despised enemies of her faith', 'Jora serves as the primary priestess at the Temple of Talos in Windhelm, one of the last remaining active Talos temples in Skyrim. Her duties include maintaining the temple, providing blessings, offering spiritual guidance to visitors, and preserving the traditions of Talos worship.', '* Extensive knowledge of Talos lore and religious traditions * Practiced in the rites and rituals of the Nine Divines * Competent in basic self-defense with a dagger * Skilled in providing spiritual counsel and comfort to the faithful * Administrative abilities in managing temple operations', 'Jora speaks with the measured tone of a religious authority, her words carrying the weight of conviction and years of devotional study. She often incorporates references to Talos and religious teachings in her speech, using formal language tempered with practical Nord sensibilities.', '* Preserve the worship of Talos despite the Empire''s ban * Protect the Temple of Talos in Windhelm from Thalmor interference * Guide and support the faithful through these challenging times * Maintain the traditions and teachings of Talos for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jordis_the_sword-maiden', 'Jordis the Sword-Maiden is a proud Nord warrior who serves as housecarl to the Thane of Solitude, embodying the martial traditions and unwavering loyalty valued by her people. Her dedication to protecting her charge and Solitude''s interests reflects both her intense training in the Solitude guard and her personal code of honor as a Nord warrior.', 'nord, warrior, noble, haafingar, legion, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Jordis trained from a young age with the city guard, displaying exceptional skill with blade and shield. Her outstanding service and dedication caught the attention of Elisif the Fair and her court, leading to her selection as housecarl for the position of Thane. She has served in the Solitude guard during the Civil War period, maintaining her loyalty to both her city and the Empire.', 'Jordis exhibits the characteristic Nord traits of pride, honor, and straightforward honesty, but tempers these with the diplomatic awareness expected of one serving in Solitude''s court. She is fiercely protective of her charge and takes her duties as housecarl with utmost seriousness, while maintaining a respectful and professional demeanor that reflects her upbringing in Skyrim''s capital.', 'Jordis is a tall, athletic Nord woman with the strong build typical of a warrior who has spent years in combat training. She has blonde hair and the fair complexion common to Nords, with subtle battle scars that speak to her experience as a warrior.', '* Elisif the Fair - Respects and serves the Jarl of Solitude with unwavering loyalty * Solitude Guard - Maintains strong ties with her former brothers and sisters in arms * Falk Firebeard - Professional relationship with Solitude''s steward who oversees court appointments * Thane of Solitude - Sworn to protect and serve with her life', 'As housecarl to the Thane of Solitude, Jordis serves as both a personal guard and sworn warrior-servant. Her duties include protecting her Thane''s life and property, offering martial support in combat, and maintaining their holdings in Solitude.', '* Expert in sword and shield combat techniques, particularly in the Imperial Legion style * Highly trained in heavy armor combat and defensive tactics * Proficient in household management and the protocols of Solitude''s court * Skilled in battlefield tactics and guard deployment strategies', 'Jordis speaks with the direct, honest manner of a Nord warrior, but maintains the formal politeness expected of someone serving in Solitude''s court. Her vocabulary reflects both military training and exposure to diplomatic discourse.', '* Serve her Thane with absolute loyalty and dedication * Uphold the honor and traditions of Solitude''s warrior culture * Protect Solitude''s interests during the ongoing civil war * Advance her martial skills to better serve her charge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jorgen', 'Jorgen is a pragmatic Nord lumberjack who runs the Morthal lumber mill, carrying both the responsibility of his business and the ancient family duty of protecting a piece of Mehrunes'' Razor. A descendant of the Axe-Bearer clan, he represents the practical, hardworking spirit of Skyrim''s common folk while secretly safeguarding a dangerous Daedric artifact.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born into the Axe-Bearer clan, Jorgen inherited both the family''s lumbering tradition and their sacred duty to protect the hilt of Mehrunes'' Razor, which has been in their possession for eight generations. He established himself in Morthal, building a life around the lumber mill and eventually marrying Lami, the local alchemist. His family''s long-standing presence in the area has given him deep roots in the community while maintaining a cautious distance from its politics.', 'Jorgen is a no-nonsense, practical man who values hard work and privacy above all else. He maintains a suspicious attitude toward outsiders and shows little interest in matters beyond his immediate responsibilities. Though he can be gruff and short-tempered with those who waste his time, he demonstrates unwavering loyalty to his family traditions and takes his hereditary duties seriously.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered features and muscular build typical of someone who spends their days performing physical labor. His hands are calloused from years of woodworking, and his face shows the marks of prolonged exposure to the elements.', '* Lami - His wife and owner of the local alchemy shop * Clan Axe-Bearer - His extended family lineage, though distant * Idgrod Ravencrone - Distrusts the Jarl''s leadership and mystical tendencies * Falion - Shares the town''s general suspicion of the mysterious wizard * Hroggar - Fellow townsman whom he distrusts after the suspicious house fire', 'Jorgen serves as Morthal''s primary lumberjack and mill operator, responsible for processing the region''s timber needs. His position is vital to the local economy, providing building materials and firewood to the hold''s residents.', '* Expert woodcutter and lumber mill operator * Capable swordsman for self-defense * Knowledge of timber assessment and processing * Basic trading and business management abilities * Experience in securing and protecting valuable artifacts', 'Jorgen speaks in a direct, often brusque manner, using simple language focused on practical matters. His tone is generally dismissive or impatient with strangers, though he becomes more earnest when discussing serious matters like his family legacy.', '* Maintain the successful operation of his lumber mill * Protect the family heirloom (Mehrunes'' Razor hilt) from falling into the wrong hands * Preserve his privacy and independence from local political conflicts * Ensure the continued prosperity and safety of his household');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jorleif', 'Jorleif is a dedicated and pragmatic Nord steward who serves as Jarl Ulfric Stormcloak''s trusted advisor in Windhelm. Despite his lack of military expertise, he provides valuable counsel on administrative matters and city governance, maintaining a delicate balance between loyal service and independent thought that his jarl appreciates.', 'nord, noble, whiterun, legion, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Jorleif worked his way up through administrative positions in the Palace of the Kings before being appointed as steward. His long-standing relationship with Ulfric Stormcloak predates the Civil War, and he has witnessed firsthand the transformation of Windhelm from a regular hold capital to the headquarters of the Stormcloak rebellion.', 'Jorleif is diplomatic and practical, preferring straightforward solutions to complex problems. He maintains a professional demeanor while being approachable to citizens, and though loyal to Ulfric, he''s not afraid to voice differing opinions. His pragmatic nature allows him to adapt to changing political circumstances, as evidenced by his ability to continue serving under Imperial rule if Windhelm falls.', 'Jorleif is a middle-aged Nord with the sturdy build typical of his race, though somewhat softened by his administrative lifestyle. His features show signs of aging from years of stress managing city affairs, with visible worry lines on his face. He maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting his position as steward.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Longtime employer and confidant, though their relationship remains professional * Galmar Stone-Fist - Professional associate and fellow advisor to Ulfric * Palace Staff - Oversees their work and maintains cordial working relationships * Windhelm Citizens - Serves as their primary point of contact for city administrative matters * Brunwulf Free-Winter - Adapts to serve under him if Imperial forces capture Windhelm', 'As steward of Windhelm, Jorleif manages the day-to-day operations of both the Palace of the Kings and the city itself. His duties include handling property sales, issuing bounties, managing the palace staff, and advising the Jarl on civilian matters. He maintains a strict daily schedule, dividing his time between administrative tasks and his advisory role.', '* Excellent administrative and organizational abilities * Strong diplomatic skills and political acumen * Proficient in record-keeping and financial management * Basic self-defense capabilities with a dagger * Experienced in property management and civil governance', 'Jorleif speaks in a formal yet accessible manner, using clear and direct language appropriate for his position. His tone is respectful and measured, though he becomes noticeably more relaxed when discussing non-official matters.', '* Maintain efficient administration of Windhelm regardless of political climate * Preserve the stability and prosperity of the city during turbulent times * Balance loyalty to Ulfric with the practical needs of Windhelm''s citizens * Ensure smooth transition of power if political leadership changes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jorn', 'Jorn is an ambitious Nord bard-in-training at the Bards College in Solitude who dreams of combining his musical talents with military service in the Imperial Legion. A passionate drummer and storyteller, he stands out for his belief that bards are the true makers of history through their chronicles, not just mere entertainers.', 'nord, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Jorn developed a deep appreciation for both martial and musical traditions of the Nord people. He enrolled in the Bards College to master the art of drumming and storytelling, while harboring dreams of using these skills to inspire Imperial troops in battle. His responsibility for preparing the King Olaf effigy suggests he has earned a position of trust within the college.', 'Confident and enthusiastic, Jorn believes in the power of instinct and passion over rigid technical precision. He exhibits a romantic streak, both in his approach to music and his subtle attraction to fellow student Illdi. Despite his respect for authority, he isn''t afraid to question traditional methods, particularly regarding Viarmo''s reserved teaching style.', 'A typical Nord male with the strong, sturdy build characteristic of his race. His hands show the calluses of countless hours of drum practice, while his posture reflects his military aspirations with a straight-backed, disciplined bearing.', '* Viarmo - Respected but sometimes frustrated instructor who teaches him drumming * Illdi - Fellow student whom he secretly admires * Pantea Ateia - Demanding instructor he strives to impress * Inge Six-Fingers - Professor who evaluates his performances * Giraud Gemane - Professor overseeing his classical studies * Ataf - Fellow student and confidant', 'Student at the Bards College with specific responsibilities for festival preparations, particularly the creation of the King Olaf effigy. He maintains a dual focus on his studies as a bard while preparing himself for a future military career with the Imperial Legion.', '* Accomplished drummer with particular talent for martial rhythms and war songs * Skilled vocalist trained in the bardic traditions * Competent swordsman, maintaining combat readiness for his planned Legion service * Storyteller and poet with focus on historical war epics * Festival organizer with experience in effigy preparation', 'Speaks with confidence and enthusiasm, often using musical metaphors and references to historical epics. His manner of speech reflects both his formal bardic training and his martial aspirations, frequently emphasizing themes of honor and victory.', '* Graduate from the Bards College with distinction * Join the Imperial Legion as a war-drummer and inspire troops in battle * Perfect his unique style of passionate, instinct-driven drumming * Earn recognition for his interpretation of classical tales through percussion * Perhaps win the affections of Illdi');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jouane_manette', 'Jouane Manette is a retired Imperial Legion healer who found a peaceful life in Rorikstead alongside his friend Rorik, whom he saved during the Great War. Despite his outward appearance as a simple advisor to Rorik, he secretly maintains his magical practice by teaching the young village girl Sissel, while helping maintain Rorikstead''s unusual prosperity.', 'breton, mage, whiterun, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Jouane trained extensively in the healing arts before joining the Imperial Legion as a combat medic during the Great War. His defining moment came when he saved the life of Rorik, a gravely wounded soldier who would become his lifelong friend, leading them both to settle in what would become Rorikstead after the war''s end.', 'Jouane is a cautious and wise individual who carefully balances his magical nature with the need to maintain peace in a rural Nordic community. He shows great compassion in his secret mentorship of Sissel, while maintaining a diplomatic approach to village politics and displaying the patience and measured judgment that comes with age and experience.', 'An elderly Breton of average height with the typical slight build of his race, showing the physical signs of his advanced age. His face bears the wrinkles and weathering of someone who has spent considerable time outdoors in Skyrim''s harsh climate, though he maintains good posture and movement despite his years.', '* Rorik - Closest friend and companion, saved his life during the Great War * Sissel - Secret magical apprentice whom he teaches and protects * Lemkil - Tense relationship due to his mistreatment of Sissel * Rorikstead Villagers - Respected elder though they remain unaware of his magical activities', 'Serves as Rorik''s trusted advisor and unofficial steward of Rorikstead, helping manage the village''s affairs and maintaining its prosperity. Secretly continues his role as a mage through clandestine teaching sessions with Sissel.', '* Expert in Restoration magic and healing techniques * Knowledgeable in agricultural magic and earth manipulation * Experienced battlefield medic with trauma treatment expertise * Diplomatic and administrative abilities from years of advising Rorik * Basic combat training from Imperial Legion service', 'Speaks in a measured, educated manner with the careful consideration of someone who weighs their words. His tone is gentle and paternal, often incorporating subtle wisdom from his years of experience while maintaining a diplomatic restraint.', '* Preserve and protect Rorikstead''s unusual prosperity while keeping its magical nature secret * Continue teaching magic to Sissel while ensuring her safety and development * Maintain peace and stability in the village during the dragon crisis * Protect his friendship with Rorik and their shared legacy in the community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('julienne_lylvieve', 'Julienne Lylvieve is an ambitious young Breton woman working at the Four Shields Inn in Dragon Bridge, dedicating herself to learning the innkeeper''s trade under Faida''s mentorship. Despite the troubled times of civil war and dragon attacks, she maintains an optimistic outlook while pursuing her dream of owning her own establishment.', 'breton, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Dragon Bridge to Azzada and Michel Lylvieve, Julienne grew up in a close-knit family environment helping with household duties from an early age. Her interest in hospitality developed through observing travelers and merchants passing through Dragon Bridge, leading her to seek apprenticeship under Faida at the Four Shields Inn.', 'Julienne is diligent, responsible, and eager to learn, demonstrating strong work ethic in her daily duties. She maintains a cheerful and pleasant demeanor despite challenging times, showing maturity beyond her years in her approach to both work and personal relationships. Her curiosity and attention to detail make her well-suited to the hospitality trade.', 'A young Breton woman in her early twenties with the characteristic slight build and medium height of her race. Her features reflect her mixed heritage, with the angular facial structure common to Bretons and likely fair complexion suited to High Rock''s climate.', '* Faida - Mentor and employer who teaches her the innkeeper''s trade * Azzada Lylvieve - Father who supports her career aspirations * Michel Lylvieve - Mother who taught her household management skills * Clinton Lylvieve - Brother with whom she shares family duties * Tasius Tragus - Possible romantic interest (removed from final game but suggested in game files)', 'Julienne works as an assistant innkeeper at the Four Shields Inn, performing various duties including sweeping, tending the hearth, serving customers, and learning business management. Her position involves both practical tasks and apprenticeship training under Faida''s guidance.', '* Proficient in hospitality management and customer service * Capable of maintaining inn facilities and performing household duties * Basic combat ability with an iron dagger for self-defense * Experienced in food service and inventory management * Developing business administration and accounting skills', 'Julienne speaks clearly and professionally, with the politeness expected of someone in the service industry. Her dialogue reflects both respect for authority figures and quiet confidence in her abilities, often using formal address like ''Miss Faida'' when speaking to her mentor.', '* Own and operate her own inn establishment * Master all aspects of inn management under Faida''s tutelage * Maintain family relationships while pursuing professional aspirations * Build a reputation as a respected innkeeper in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jurgen_windcaller', 'Jurgen Windcaller was a legendary Nord hero and warrior who fundamentally transformed the use of the Thu''um among his people after experiencing a profound spiritual awakening. Following the devastating defeat at Red Mountain, he founded the Greybeards and established the Way of the Voice, forever changing how the power of the Voice would be used in Nordic culture.', 'nord', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born during the height of the First Empire of the Nords, Jurgen Windcaller rose to prominence as a mighty Tongue and war leader who wielded the Thu''um in battle. After leading Nordic forces to a crushing defeat at Red Mountain, he spent seven years meditating on the meaning of his failure, ultimately receiving divine inspiration about the true purpose of the Voice. This revelation led him to establish High Hrothgar and found the Greybeards, dedicating the rest of his life to teaching the Way of the Voice.', 'Jurgen Windcaller is characterized by his profound wisdom, solemn demeanor, and unwavering dedication to spiritual enlightenment. His transformation from warrior to philosopher demonstrates his capacity for deep introspection and humility, while his establishment of the Greybeards shows his commitment to sharing spiritual knowledge. He maintains a stern but patient approach to teaching, emphasizing the importance of discipline and meditation in mastering the Voice.', 'A tall, imposing Nord with the bearing of both a warrior and a sage, weathered by years of meditation and exposure to the harsh climate of High Hrothgar. His physical presence combines the strength of his warrior past with the serene dignity of a spiritual master.', '* The Greybeards - Founder and first master of their order * Kyne/Kynareth - Deep spiritual connection as the divine source of the Voice * Paarthurnax - Likely early relationship as the dragon began teaching humans the Voice * Fellow Tongues - Former companions in battle before his spiritual transformation * The Last Dragonborn - Spiritual successor who seeks his horn', 'Jurgen Windcaller served as the founder and first leader of the Greybeards, establishing their monastery at High Hrothgar. In death, he continues his role as a spiritual guide in Sovngarde, counseling those who seek wisdom about the Way of the Voice.', '* Master of the Thu''um with unprecedented understanding of its spiritual nature * Exceptional warrior and military leader during his early life * Profound meditation and philosophical contemplation abilities * Teacher and mentor capable of transmitting complex spiritual concepts * Deep understanding of Nordic traditions and religious practices', 'Speaks with measured, philosophical wisdom using formal and often cryptic language that reflects deep spiritual understanding. His words carry the weight of ancient Nordic tradition and divine insight, often delivered in a solemn, poetic manner.', '* Guide others to understand and respect the true purpose of the Voice as a means of honoring the gods * Preserve the Way of the Voice through his disciples, the Greybeards * Ensure that those who wield the Thu''um do so with wisdom and proper spiritual understanding * Maintain the sacred balance between power and restraint in the use of the Voice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('jyrik_gauldurson', 'Jyrik Gauldurson is the eldest and most magically adept of the three infamous Gauldur brothers, ancient Nordic sorcerers who murdered their father to steal his powerful amulet. A formidable draugr lord sealed away in Saarthal, he maintains a mystical connection to an ancient magical orb that grants him temporary invulnerability and mastery over elemental magic.', 'nord', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born as the eldest son of the renowned Arch-Mage Gauldur during the First Era, Jyrik grew up studying magic and developing his arcane talents. After discovering the source of his father''s power in a mysterious amulet, he orchestrated his father''s murder alongside his brothers, leading to a reign of terror across Nordic villages until their eventual defeat by Arch-Mage Geirmund and his battlemages.', 'Jyrik is arrogant and power-hungry, believing his magical abilities make him superior to others. He displays contempt for those who challenge him and maintains an air of aristocratic superiority even in undeath. His obsession with magical power and his father''s amulet has persisted beyond death, driving his actions even as a draugr.', 'As a draugr, Jyrik appears as a tall, desiccated Nordic corpse with sunken features and glowing blue eyes characteristic of powerful undead. His withered form still carries the bearing of a noble, and his movements remain fluid and purposeful despite his undead state.', '* Gauldur - His father, whom he murdered in pursuit of power * Sigdis Gauldurson - Younger brother and fellow conspirator * Mikrul Gauldurson - Youngest brother and conspirator * Arch-Mage Geirmund - Primary adversary who defeated and sealed him away * Tolfdir - Current nemesis who aids in his defeat at Saarthal', 'Originally a Nordic sorcerer and nobleman, Jyrik now exists as an undead guardian of Saarthal, bound to the magical orb that sustains his power. His role as a draugr lord involves defending ancient Nordic secrets and magical artifacts within the ruins.', '* Master of elemental magic with the ability to switch between fire, frost, and storm resistances * Powerful connection to ancient magical artifacts, particularly the orb in Saarthal * Skilled in ancient Nordic combat techniques with proficiency in both magic and weapons * Ability to maintain consciousness and magical abilities even in undeath * Command over lesser draugr and undead within his domain', 'Jyrik speaks in archaic Nordic patterns with a deep, resonating voice that carries magical power. His speech is filled with arrogant proclamations and ancient terms, often mocking his opponents while emphasizing his own power and noble heritage.', '* Maintain his connection to the magical orb in Saarthal to preserve his power * Prevent intruders from claiming his portion of Gauldur''s amulet * Reunite with his brothers to restore their combined power * Defend the ancient secrets of Saarthal from those he deems unworthy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kai_wet-pommel', 'Kai Wet-Pommel is a high-ranking Stormcloak officer stationed in Winterhold who serves as a key military leader and recruiter for Ulfric''s rebellion. A passionate Nord nationalist and skilled warrior, he embodies the ideological fervor of the Stormcloak cause while maintaining tactical oversight of their operations in the region.', 'nord, warrior, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Winterhold before its decline, Kai witnessed firsthand the gradual erosion of Nord traditions and power under Imperial rule. His family''s long military history and the collapse of Winterhold''s prominence likely shaped his strong nationalist views and eventual allegiance to Ulfric Stormcloak''s cause. He rose through the Stormcloak ranks through a combination of martial prowess and unwavering loyalty.', 'Kai is a zealous true believer in the Stormcloak cause, combining nationalist fervor with military discipline. He exhibits a black-and-white worldview that categorizes people as either true sons of Skyrim or enemies, showing little patience for neutral stances or Imperial sympathizers. Despite his hardline views, he maintains a sense of honor and brotherhood with fellow Stormcloaks.', 'A sturdy Nord warrior with the weathered features typical of someone who has spent years in Winterhold''s harsh climate. His body bears the scars and muscular build of a seasoned soldier, with callused hands from years of weapons training.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Revered leader and true High King in Kai''s eyes * Galmar Stone-Fist - Superior officer and military commander * Winterhold Guards - Commands their loyalty when stationed in the city * Imperial Legion - Bitter enemies seen as betrayers of Skyrim * Thalmor - Despised enemies representing everything he fights against', 'Kai serves as a high-ranking Stormcloak officer responsible for military operations and recruitment in the Winterhold region. He splits his duties between tactical planning in the war room and maintaining Stormcloak control over his assigned territory, whether from the Jarl''s Longhouse or the backup camp.', '* Proficient with both two-handed weapons and sword-and-shield combat styles * Experienced archer with hunting and combat applications * Military tactical and strategic planning expertise * Leadership and recruitment capabilities * Survival skills honed in Winterhold''s harsh environment', 'Kai speaks with a strong Nordic accent and uses direct, unambiguous language that reflects his military background and strong convictions. His speech often includes references to honor, tradition, and brotherhood, while expressing contempt for those he views as enemies of Skyrim.', '* See Ulfric Stormcloak crowned as the true High King of Skyrim * Drive the Imperial Legion and Thalmor influence from Skyrim completely * Restore traditional Nord values and governance to their homeland * Rebuild Winterhold''s prominence as a strong Nord city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kaie', 'Kaie is a fierce and dedicated Forsworn operative who serves as a crucial link between Madanach and the outside world during the Cidhna Mine prison break. As a Breton nightblade, she combines magical abilities with combat skills to serve the Forsworn cause, demonstrating unwavering loyalty to her people''s struggle to reclaim the Reach.', 'breton, warrior, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born into the Forsworn culture, Kaie was raised among the native people of the Reach during their ongoing conflict with the Nords. She likely witnessed the violent suppression of her people by Ulfric Stormcloak and his forces, which solidified her dedication to the Forsworn cause and led her to become one of Madanach''s most trusted operatives.', 'Kaie exhibits a pragmatic and ruthless demeanor, showing no hesitation in eliminating obstacles to the Forsworn cause. She demonstrates unwavering loyalty to Madanach and the Forsworn movement, coupled with a efficient, task-oriented mindset that prioritizes results over moral considerations.', 'As a Breton woman, Kaie possesses the typical slight build and medium height characteristic of her race. Unlike many Forsworn, she lacks their distinctive facial tattoos, suggesting she may operate more frequently in civilized areas where such marks would draw attention. Her face bears the weathered look of someone who spends considerable time in the harsh conditions of the Reach.', '* Madanach - Direct superior and leader whom she serves with absolute loyalty * Cidhna Mine Forsworn - Fellow warriors she aids in their escape * Markarth Guard - Adversaries she actively works against * Druadach Redoubt Forsworn - Fellow tribal members she lives among * Nordic authorities - Sworn enemies of her people and cause', 'Kaie serves as a high-ranking Forsworn operative, acting as both a warrior and covert agent. Her duties include maintaining supply lines, coordinating with outside agents, and executing tactical operations for the Forsworn leadership.', '* Proficient in nightblade combat techniques combining stealth and magic * Skilled in Alteration magic, particularly protective spells like Oakflesh * Capable necromancer with knowledge of Raise Zombie * Destruction magic practitioner specializing in fire spells * Expert in covert operations and equipment procurement * Accomplished warrior with both one-handed weapons and light armor', 'Kaie speaks in direct, unembellished statements that reflect her militant mindset and dedication to efficiency. Her tone is typically stern and matter-of-fact, with occasional outbursts of passionate battle cries when fighting for the Forsworn cause.', '* Aid in the liberation of the Reach from Nordic control * Support Madanach''s leadership and the greater Forsworn movement * Strengthen the Forsworn''s hold on their ancestral lands * Eliminate those who oppose the Forsworn cause * Preserve the old ways and traditions of her people');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('karita', 'Karita is a hardworking Nord merchant who has established herself as a respected vendor in Whiterun''s marketplace. She represents the entrepreneurial spirit of Skyrim''s merchant class while maintaining strong traditional Nord values and family ties.', 'nord, merchant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun Hold, Karita learned the merchant trade from her parents who were traveling traders. She settled in Whiterun after marrying Hodor, choosing to establish a permanent market stall rather than continue the nomadic trading lifestyle of her youth.', 'Karita is a warm and engaging merchant who takes genuine pride in her wares and knowledge of local trade. She maintains a perfect balance between shrewd business sense and friendly demeanor, while her strong Nord values of family and tradition guide her daily life.', 'Karita is a sturdy Nord woman in her early thirties with the characteristic fair complexion of her race. She has strong, weathered hands from years of handling merchandise, and her face shows subtle laugh lines around her eyes from her frequent warm smiles.', '* Hodor - Beloved husband and partner in both life and business * Lars - Their young child whom she dotes on frequently * Other Market Vendors - Maintains cordial professional relationships * Regular Customers - Has built a loyal following among Whiterun''s citizens', 'Karita operates a successful market stall in Whiterun''s Plains District, where she sells a variety of general goods and sundries. She manages all aspects of her business, from procurement and inventory to sales and customer relations.', '* Expert haggling and bartering abilities * Keen eye for quality merchandise and fair pricing * Knowledge of trade routes and market values throughout Whiterun Hold * Basic accounting and inventory management', 'Speaks with a pronounced Nord accent, often using traditional phrases and colloquialisms common to Whiterun Hold. Her tone is warm and inviting, though she can be firm when negotiating prices.', '* Expand her business to become one of Whiterun''s premier merchants * Provide a stable and prosperous future for her child Lars * Eventually open a proper shop within the city walls');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('karl', 'Karl is a hardworking but troubled Nord miner in Dawnstar who battles with alcoholism while maintaining his position at Iron-Breaker Mine. Despite his drinking habits interfering with his work, he maintains a cynical yet honest perspective on life, openly defying his employer''s wishes while still managing to fulfill his duties.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born and raised in Dawnstar, Karl found work in the mines as a young man and has spent his entire adult life working the iron veins of the region. His drinking habit developed over years of harsh working conditions and the perpetual darkness of working night shifts, eventually becoming a coping mechanism for the difficult lifestyle of a miner in Skyrim''s unforgiving northern coast.', 'Karl exhibits a rebellious and cynical nature, openly defying authority while maintaining a strong work ethic despite his alcoholism. He shows signs of being world-weary and jaded, particularly regarding the petty feuds of his employers, yet maintains enough self-awareness to acknowledge his drinking problem. His cynicism is balanced by a surprising honesty about his faults and a dedication to his work that persists despite his vices.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of someone who spends their days wielding a pickaxe. His face likely shows the weathering effects of working outdoors in Dawnstar''s harsh climate, with calloused hands and the slight tremor characteristic of long-term alcohol use.', '* Beitild - Antagonistic relationship with his employer who disapproves of his drinking * Leigelf - Neutral relationship with Beitild''s ex-husband, though drawn unwillingly into their feud * Irgnir - Fellow miner with whom he potentially shares living quarters * Thoring - Proprietor of Windpeak Inn who serves him regularly', 'Karl works as a full-time miner at Iron-Breaker Mine, splitting his time between mining iron ore and operating the smelter. His unusual schedule has him working through the night in the mine and spending twelve hours at the smelter during the day, making him one of the hardest-working miners in Dawnstar despite his drinking habits.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of iron ore extraction * Skilled smelter operator capable of processing raw ore into ingots * Physical endurance to work long hours under harsh conditions * Functional alcoholic able to maintain productivity despite regular drinking', 'Karl speaks in a direct, unfiltered manner with a typical Nordic accent, often expressing cynicism and weariness. His speech patterns suggest someone educated enough to articulate his thoughts clearly but common enough to use casual language.', '* Maintain his position at the mine while preserving his independence and drinking habits * Earn enough septims to support his lifestyle and drinking * Avoid getting caught in the middle of Beitild and Leigelf''s feud * Find some peace despite his inability to sleep well due to Dawnstar''s shared nightmares');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('karliah', 'Karliah is a skilled Dunmer thief and member of the secretive Nightingales, a trinity of warriors sworn to serve the Daedric Prince Nocturnal. Born of royal blood as the granddaughter of Queen Barenziah, she spent 25 years in exile after being falsely accused of murdering her lover and Guildmaster Gallus, dedicating herself to exposing Mercer Frey''s treachery and restoring honor to the Nightingales.', 'darkelf, thief, skyrimall, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_karliah', '', 'Born to Dralsi Indoril, daughter of Queen Barenziah and the Nightingale thief Drayven Indoril, Karliah was taught the art of thievery by her mother from an early age. She eventually joined the Thieves Guild in Skyrim where she fell in love with Gallus Desidenius and was inducted into the Nightingales. After Mercer Frey murdered Gallus and framed her for the crime, she spent 25 years in exile planning her revenge and protecting the Thieves Guild from afar.', 'Karliah is patient, calculating, and incredibly determined, willing to spend decades meticulously planning her return to clear her name. She maintains a calm, measured demeanor even in tense situations, but harbors deep emotional wounds from Gallus''s murder and her forced exile. Though capable of great cunning, she adheres to a personal code of honor and loyalty, especially regarding her Nightingale oath.', 'A slender Dunmer woman with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her race. Her features are sharp and angular, typical of mer heritage, but possess an elegant grace that hints at her noble bloodline. She moves with the natural fluidity and poise of a master thief.', '* Gallus Desidenius - Former lover and Guildmaster, murdered by Mercer Frey * Mercer Frey - Bitter enemy who murdered Gallus and framed her for the crime * Queen Barenziah - Maternal grandmother, though they likely had limited contact * Dralsi Indoril - Mother who taught her thieving skills * Thieves Guild - Former allies turned hostile due to Mercer''s deception * Nocturnal - Daedric Prince she serves as a Nightingale', 'Karliah serves as a Nightingale, one of three warriors sworn to protect the Twilight Sepulcher and serve Nocturnal. She operates independently as a master thief, using her skills to survive in exile while working to expose Mercer Frey''s betrayal.', '* Master archer with exceptional accuracy and stealth shooting abilities * Expert in stealth, infiltration, and shadow manipulation * Highly skilled alchemist, particularly with poisons and paralytic agents * Accomplished thief specializing in lockpicking and pickpocketing * Proficient in Nightingale abilities and shadow magic', 'Karliah speaks in a soft, measured tone with careful word choice that reflects her calculating nature. Her speech carries subtle hints of both noble refinement and street-wise practicality, often employing metaphors and lessons learned from her thieving background.', '* Clear her name and expose Mercer Frey''s betrayal to the Thieves Guild * Restore honor to the Nightingales and strengthen their connection to Nocturnal * Protect the Twilight Sepulcher and recover the Skeleton Key * Honor Gallus''s memory by returning the Thieves Guild to its former glory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('katla', 'Katla is a resilient and industrious Nord farmer who single-handedly manages one of Solitude''s most important agricultural operations. Despite being married, she has evolved into the true backbone of both her family and farm, displaying remarkable strength and dedication in keeping the capital city fed through her daily labors.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Haafingar Hold, Katla established her farm near Solitude to help support the capital''s growing food demands. She married Snilling in her younger years and gave birth to their son Knud, but over time emerged as the primary provider and worker of the family as her husband proved unsuited for physical labor. Through years of hard work, she has built her farm into a crucial source of sustenance for Solitude''s population.', 'Katla embodies the Nordic values of hard work, self-reliance, and direct honesty, taking immense pride in her agricultural contributions to Solitude. She maintains a no-nonsense approach to her work while showing warmth toward her family, displaying both authority in managing her farm and gentle humor regarding her husband''s limitations. Her belief in fair compensation for labor reveals a strong sense of justice and work ethic.', 'Katla possesses the sturdy build and physical resilience typical of Nord women, with muscles hardened by years of agricultural labor. Her face shows the weathering effects of constant outdoor work, with sun-worn features that speak to her dedication. Her hands are calloused from endless hours of farming work, marking her as someone who has earned her strength through honest labor.', '* Snilling - Husband who manages indoor work; their relationship is marked by mutual understanding and gentle humor * Knud - Beloved son who aspires to follow in her footsteps as a farmer * Solitude Guards - Professional relationship as an important food supplier * Local merchants - Business connections for selling surplus crops', 'Katla serves as the owner and primary worker of Katla''s Farm, one of Solitude''s main sources of fresh produce. Her role is vital to the city''s food supply, as she manages the cultivation and harvest of essential crops including leeks, potatoes, and wheat. She also maintains a fair employment system, paying workers who assist with harvesting.', '* Expert farmer with deep knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Proficient in physical labor and farm management * Capable of operating and maintaining farming equipment * Basic combat skills for self-defense, including dagger usage * Strong business acumen in managing farm operations', 'Katla speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of hard-working Nords, though she shows a warmer tone with family. Her speech patterns reflect her practical nature, often focusing on work-related matters with brief, to-the-point statements.', '* Maintain and expand her farm''s production to better serve Solitude''s growing population * Ensure her son Knud learns the skills necessary to eventually take over the farm * Continue providing reliable employment opportunities for local workers * Preserve her family''s agricultural legacy in Haafingar Hold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('katria', 'Katria is a Nord spirit and former adventurer whose life''s work focused on uncovering the legendary Aetherium Forge, only to have her research stolen by her treacherous apprentice before meeting her death in Arkngthamz. Even in death, she remains determined to prove her discoveries and validate her life''s work by guiding worthy adventurers to complete what she could not.', 'nord, archer, skyrimall, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Katria spent nearly twenty years as a professional adventurer and researcher, dedicating her life to tracking down evidence of the Aetherium Forge and its powerful artifacts. Her extensive research led her to Arkngthamz, where she met her demise in a tragic fall while exploring the ruins, but her spirit remained bound to the mortal plane due to her unfinished work and the betrayal she suffered.', 'Katria is initially cautious and protective of others, warning them away from the dangers that claimed her life. Once she recognizes a capable ally, she reveals herself to be knowledgeable, determined, and willing to assist, though she carries deep bitterness about her apprentice''s betrayal. Despite her ghostly state, she maintains a dry sense of humor and shows genuine concern for her living companions.', 'In her spectral form, Katria appears as a tall, athletic Nord woman with defined features typical of her race. Her transparent, ethereal form maintains the physical build of an experienced adventurer who spent years exploring Dwemer ruins.', '* Unnamed Apprentice - Former student who betrayed her by stealing and publishing her research * The Last Dragonborn - Potential ally in completing her life''s work * Various Scholars - Academic connections who may have doubted her theories about the Aetherium Forge', 'Katria was a professional adventurer and researcher specializing in Dwemer artifacts and history, particularly focused on the legendary Aetherium Forge. In death, she serves as a spiritual guide to those seeking to complete her research.', '* Expert in Dwemer history, architecture, and artifacts * Accomplished archer and wielder of her unique bow, Zephyr * Skilled explorer with extensive knowledge of ruin navigation * Experienced researcher with deep understanding of ancient Nordic and Dwemer writings', 'Katria speaks with a mix of scholarly knowledge and practical experience, often using dry humor to mask her tragic circumstances. Her tone alternates between cautionary warning and enthusiastic sharing of her expertise, particularly regarding Dwemer technology and history.', '* Prove the validity of her research about the Aetherium Forge * Guide a worthy adventurer to complete her life''s work * Achieve recognition for her discoveries and clear her name from her apprentice''s plagiarism * Find peace and resolution to finally rest');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('keeper_carcette', 'Keeper Carcette is the formidable leader of the Vigilants of Stendarr in Skyrim, serving as both a spiritual guide and military commander for the order. A master of Restoration magic and skilled warrior-priest, she dedicates her life to hunting daedra worshippers and protecting the innocent through Stendarr''s mercy and justice.', 'breton, priest, pale, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born to a noble Breton family with strong ties to the Temple of Stendarr, Carcette demonstrated exceptional aptitude for Restoration magic from an early age. After the Oblivion Crisis, she joined the newly-formed Vigilants of Stendarr, quickly rising through their ranks due to her unwavering dedication and leadership abilities. Her appointment as Keeper of the Vigil in Skyrim came after years of distinguished service combating daedric influences across High Rock and Skyrim.', 'Carcette exhibits a stern and uncompromising devotion to Stendarr''s teachings, viewing the world through a strict lens of justice and mercy. While capable of great compassion toward the innocent and her fellow Vigilants, she shows zero tolerance for daedra worship or supernatural threats. She carries herself with the quiet authority of someone accustomed to command, tempering her militant stance with wisdom and patience when training new recruits.', 'A middle-aged Breton woman with sharp, weathered features that reflect years of vigilant service. Her athletic build and excellent posture speak to her warrior training, while her hands bear the subtle magical calluses common to experienced Restoration mages. Her face shows signs of frequent exposure to Skyrim''s harsh climate, with striking grey eyes that seem to pierce through deception.', '* Vigilant Tolan - Trusted subordinate and veteran member of the order * Brother Adalvald - Respected scholar within the Vigilants * The Circle of Vigilants - Her direct council of senior members * Daedra Worshippers - Sworn enemies to be converted or brought to justice * College of Winterhold - Maintains cautious diplomatic relations regarding magical matters', 'As Keeper of the Vigil in Skyrim, Carcette oversees all Vigilant operations in the province from the Hall of the Vigilant. She manages recruitment, training, and deployment of Vigilants while personally handling the most serious cases of daedric corruption. Her position requires her to balance administrative duties with active field leadership and magical instruction.', '* Master-level practitioner of Restoration magic, specializing in healing and anti-undead spells * Expert combat training with warhammers and heavy armor * Accomplished teacher of magical and martial disciplines * Extensive knowledge of daedric cults and their practices * Skilled administrator and tactical commander', 'Speaks with clear authority and precise diction, favoring formal language that reflects her noble upbringing and leadership position. Her tone carries both the warmth of a healer and the stern conviction of a warrior-priest, switching between them as circumstances demand.', '* Eradicate all daedric influence from Skyrim * Expand the Vigilants'' presence and influence throughout the province * Train the next generation of Vigilants to carry on Stendarr''s mission * Maintain peaceful relations with Skyrim''s other religious and magical institutions while upholding Vigilant principles');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('keerava', 'Keerava is a hardened Argonian innkeeper who runs The Bee and Barb in Riften with an iron grip and unwavering vigilance. Despite her tough exterior and cynical outlook, she maintains a successful business in the corrupt city while dreaming of a better life with her partner Talen-Jei.', 'argonian, innkeeper, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleargonian', '', 'Originally from Black Marsh, Keerava migrated to Skyrim seeking business opportunities and eventually settled in Riften. She worked her way up from serving drinks to owning The Bee and Barb, learning harsh lessons about survival in the crime-ridden city along the way. Her experiences with the Thieves Guild and local corruption have made her particularly cautious and distrustful.', 'Keerava is tough, pragmatic, and perpetually vigilant, never letting her guard down even to sleep. While outwardly gruff and sometimes hostile, she harbors a softer side that shows in her relationship with Talen-Jei and her dream of a better life. She''s a shrewd businesswoman who knows how to navigate Riften''s dangerous political landscape while maintaining her independence.', 'A female Argonian with dark green scales and amber eyes, showing signs of age and stress around her face. Her posture is always alert and tense, ready to deal with any trouble that might arise in her establishment. Her hands are rough from years of working behind the bar.', '* Talen-Jei - Romantic partner and business associate who shares her dream of leaving Riften * Thieves Guild - Complex relationship as both victim and reluctant associate * Maven Black-Briar - Cautious business relationship, aware of her influence * Regular Patrons - Professional but guarded relationships * Local Guards - Maintains cordial relations for protection', 'Keerava is the owner and proprietor of The Bee and Barb, one of Riften''s most prominent taverns. She manages all aspects of the business, from serving drinks and renting rooms to maintaining order and handling finances, working tirelessly around the clock.', '* Expert at business management and accounting * Proficient in self-defense with daggers * Skilled at reading people and detecting trouble * Advanced knowledge of drink mixing and food preparation * Expert at negotiating and handling difficult customers', 'Keerava speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a slight Argonian accent, often punctuating her statements with cynical observations about Riften. Her tone is typically brusque and businesslike, though she softens somewhat when speaking with Talen-Jei.', '* Save enough money to leave Riften and start a new life elsewhere with Talen-Jei * Maintain independence from the Thieves Guild and Black-Briar influence * Keep The Bee and Barb as a respectable establishment despite Riften''s corruption * Secure a stable future free from the city''s criminal elements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kematu', 'Kematu is a skilled and authoritative Redguard warrior who leads a contingent of Alik''r fighters on a mission to apprehend a noble fugitive from Hammerfell. As a seasoned commander of these desert warriors, he combines diplomatic finesse with martial prowess while pursuing justice for his homeland.', 'redguard, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Hammerfell, Kematu rose through the ranks of the Alik''r warriors through demonstrated leadership and combat excellence. He earned his position as a commander during the resistance against the Aldmeri Dominion, developing expertise in tracking fugitives and maintaining order. His current mission to capture Saadia represents a crucial assignment from the noble houses of Taneth, who trust him to bring justice to those who betrayed Hammerfell during the Great War.', 'Kematu exhibits a calm, calculated demeanor that masks his lethal capabilities as a warrior. He values diplomacy and prefers to resolve conflicts through negotiation rather than violence, though he won''t hesitate to employ force when necessary. His strong sense of justice and loyalty to Hammerfell drives his actions, while his leadership style emphasizes discipline and honor.', 'A weathered Redguard man with a muscular, athletic build honed through years of desert warfare and training. His face bears the subtle scars of combat experience, with sharp, observant eyes that constantly assess his surroundings. His physical presence commands respect, reflecting his role as a military leader.', '* Alik''r Warriors - Loyal subordinates who follow his command without question * Noble Houses of Taneth - Employers who trust him with bringing traitors to justice * Saadia/Iman - Primary target and alleged traitor to Hammerfell * Whiterun Guards - Tense relationship due to their suspicion of Alik''r presence', 'Kematu serves as a commander of the Alik''r warriors, specializing in tracking down fugitives and enforcing justice on behalf of Hammerfell''s noble houses. His role combines elements of military leadership, investigation, and diplomatic representation of Hammerfell''s interests abroad.', '* Master swordsman specializing in traditional Redguard curved sword techniques * Expert tactician and military commander * Skilled diplomat capable of negotiating complex situations * Proficient tracker with extensive experience hunting fugitives * Advanced hand-to-hand combat training', 'Kematu speaks with formal, measured tones that reflect his educated background and leadership position. His diplomatic yet authoritative manner of speech demonstrates both his noble connections and military discipline.', '* Capture Saadia and return her to Hammerfell to face justice for her crimes * Maintain the honor and reputation of the Alik''r warriors in foreign lands * Strengthen Hammerfell''s resistance against the Aldmeri Dominion * Uphold justice and protect his homeland''s interests');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kerah', 'Kerah is a skilled Redguard merchant who runs a successful jewelry stall in Markarth''s marketplace, selling fine silver pieces crafted by her husband Endon. She represents the intersection of traditional Redguard craftsmanship and Markarth''s silver trade, maintaining her family''s business while navigating the city''s complex political climate.', 'redguard, merchant, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in a Redguard family with strong ties to silversmithing, Kerah married Endon and settled in Markarth to establish their jewelry business. Together they built a reputation for quality craftsmanship while raising two children, maintaining their cultural heritage while adapting to life in the Reach. Their success has persisted despite the increasing control of the Silver-Blood family over Markarth''s silver trade.', 'Kerah is warm and diplomatic, showing genuine enthusiasm for both her merchandise and customer interactions. She maintains a professional demeanor while dealing with Markarth''s political tensions, balancing her family''s prosperity with careful neutrality. Though proud of her Redguard heritage and family''s craftsmanship, she shows pragmatic adaptability in dealing with the city''s changing power dynamics.', 'A middle-aged Redguard woman with the characteristic dark skin and strong features of her race. She maintains a dignified bearing appropriate to a successful merchant, with well-groomed hair and careful attention to her appearance. Her hands show the subtle signs of years handling jewelry and working with merchants.', '* Endon - Beloved husband and master silversmith who crafts their merchandise * Adara - Daughter who is learning the family trade of silversmithing * Cade - Son who has joined the Stormcloak rebellion * Calcelmo - Regular customer and respected scholar in Markarth * Silver-Blood Family - Tense business relationship due to their control over the city''s silver trade', 'Kerah manages a successful jewelry stall in Markarth''s marketplace, handling sales, customer relations, and business operations. She serves as both merchant and curator of her husband''s silver craftsmanship, while also teaching her daughter the commercial aspects of their family business.', '* Expert merchant with deep knowledge of jewelry and precious metals * Skilled negotiator and saleswoman * Knowledgeable about Markarth''s history and politics * Proficient in business management and customer relations * Basic understanding of silversmithing techniques', 'Kerah speaks in a refined, professional manner with subtle hints of her Redguard accent, using persuasive but honest language to describe her wares. Her tone is warm and engaging, often personalizing her sales approach to each customer while maintaining appropriate merchant-client boundaries.', '* Ensure the continued success and legacy of her family''s jewelry business * Support her daughter Adara''s development as a silversmith * Maintain their business independence despite Silver-Blood influence * Preserve Redguard crafting traditions within Markarth''s silver trade * Hope for her son Cade''s safe return from the civil war');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kesh_the_clean', 'Kesh the Clean is a devoted Khajiit worshipper of Peryite who serves as the primary caretaker and alchemist at the Daedric Prince''s shrine in Skyrim. This skilled spellsword combines his mastery of alchemy with religious devotion, acting as an intermediary between Peryite and those seeking the Daedric Prince''s audience.', 'khajiit, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Originally a wandering Khajiit alchemist, Kesh found his calling in service to Peryite after surviving a devastating plague that claimed many of his caravan companions. His survival of the disease was interpreted as a sign of Peryite''s favor, leading him to dedicate his life to the Daedric Prince of pestilence and natural order. He established himself at the remote shrine, where he has spent years perfecting his alchemical crafts and serving as Peryite''s mortal representative.', 'Kesh exhibits a calm, methodical demeanor befitting his role as a priest of the Prince of Order. He shows an unusual fascination with disease and purification, viewing both as necessary aspects of natural order rather than purely negative forces. Despite his association with a Daedric Prince often considered malevolent, Kesh maintains a helpful and patient disposition, though his perspective on disease and suffering can seem unsettling to outsiders.', 'Like most Khajiit, Kesh possesses a feline appearance with fur-covered body and distinctive cat-like features. His fur appears well-groomed and unusually clean for someone living in such remote conditions, reflecting his nickname. He maintains an athletic build typical of a spellsword, combining physical capability with magical aptitude.', '* Peryite - Primary deity and master whom he serves with unwavering devotion * Afflicted - Views these diseased followers as blessed by Peryite * Local alchemists - Maintains loose trading relationships for rare ingredients * Pilgrims - Serves as guide and intermediary for those seeking Peryite''s audience', 'Kesh serves as both the shrine keeper and chief alchemist at the Shrine to Peryite, where he maintains the sacred site and prepares the special incense needed for communion with the Daedric Prince. He combines his religious duties with alchemical research, particularly focusing on substances related to disease and purification.', '* Expert alchemist specializing in diseases, poisons, and purification ingredients * Competent spellsword combining destructive magic with melee combat * Skilled in ritual practices and Daedric communion * Advanced knowledge of diseases and their spiritual significance * Proficient cook with expertise in traditional Khajiit cuisine', 'Kesh speaks in third person, following Khajiit custom, while employing formal language filled with metaphors relating to disease, cleansing, and natural order. His tone remains calm and measured, often including philosophical observations about the nature of purity and corruption.', '* Serve Peryite faithfully by maintaining his shrine and facilitating communion with mortals * Perfect his understanding of the relationship between disease and purification through alchemical research * Guide worthy followers to Peryite''s service and spread understanding of the Prince''s true nature * Achieve a deeper spiritual connection with Peryite through continued devotion and study');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kharag_gro-shurkul', 'Kharag gro-Shurkul is a reclusive Orsimer lumberjack who maintains the Solitude Sawmill alongside his Nord employer Hjorunn. A skilled woodworker with a complicated relationship to human society, he represents the struggle of Orsimer integration into Nordic communities while maintaining their cultural identity.', 'orc, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born to a small Orc stronghold in the mountains of Haafingar Hold, Kharag left his ancestral home seeking independence from the rigid tribal hierarchy. He found work at the Solitude Sawmill, where his natural strength and work ethic earned him a permanent position, though the prejudices of local Nords have kept him somewhat isolated from the broader community.', 'Stoic and reserved, Kharag embodies the Orcish values of hard work and personal honor while struggling with his place in Nord society. He maintains a professional demeanor but harbors deep frustrations with how Orcs are treated in human settlements, leading him to be somewhat withdrawn and defensive in social situations.', 'Kharag has the typical robust build of an Orc male, with prominent tusks and a strong, muscular frame hardened by years of physical labor. His green skin bears numerous small scars from logging work, and his black hair is kept short and practical for his profession.', '* Hjorunn - Employer with whom he has a strained but functional working relationship * Solitude Guards - Maintain a cautious distance, occasionally showing unwarranted suspicion * Local Wood Elves - Occasional trading partners for lumber-related work * Stronghold Family - Distant but not entirely severed ties to his original clan', 'As the primary worker at Solitude Sawmill, Kharag handles most of the day-to-day operations including log cutting, maintenance of equipment, and coordination with lumber merchants. His position is essential to Solitude''s lumber supply, though his contributions often go unrecognized by the city''s population.', '* Expert woodcutter with deep knowledge of lumber qualities and processing * Considerable physical strength and stamina from years of manual labor * Basic blacksmithing skills for maintaining tools and equipment * Wilderness survival abilities learned from his stronghold upbringing', 'Kharag speaks in short, direct sentences with the typical gruff Orcish accent, often dropping unnecessary words. He tends to be more verbose about work-related topics but maintains minimal conversation about personal matters.', '* Earn enough money to potentially establish his own logging operation away from city prejudices * Prove through his work that Orcs can be valuable members of Nord society * Maintain his Orcish traditions while adapting to life outside the strongholds');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kharjo', 'Kharjo is a noble Khajiit warrior serving as a caravan guard in Skyrim, bound by a debt of honor to Ahkari after being freed from imprisonment in Cyrodiil. Despite his current circumstances, he maintains dignity and martial prowess while longing for his homeland of Elsweyr, demonstrating both the pride and adaptability characteristic of his people.', 'khajiit, warrior, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born and raised in Elsweyr, Kharjo was given a Moon Amulet by his mother as a cub, his most treasured possession and connection to home. After an unfortunate incident involving gambling and drinking in Cyrodiil led to his imprisonment, he was freed by the merchant Ahkari and now works to repay this debt through loyal service as a caravan guard in the harsh lands of Skyrim.', 'Kharjo is honorable and dutiful, taking his responsibilities as a guard seriously while maintaining a philosophical outlook on life typical of Khajiit culture. He shows wisdom in his advice to others about life''s lessons, particularly regarding gambling and drink, drawing from his own past mistakes. Despite his circumstances, he maintains a dignified demeanor while displaying both practical caution and warrior''s courage.', 'Kharjo has the typical feline features of a Khajiit, with distinctive fur patterns and keen eyes adapted to both day and night vision. His physique is strong and agile, built from years of warrior training and guard duty. His movements display the natural grace of his race combined with the disciplined bearing of a trained warrior.', '* Ahkari - Employer and savior to whom he owes a life debt * Fellow Caravan Members - Trusted colleagues and traveling companions * Mother - Distant but beloved family connection, gave him his Moon Amulet * Bandits - Persistent enemies who frequently threaten the caravan * Zaynabi - Fellow caravan member with whom he shares regular dialogue', 'Kharjo serves as a professional caravan guard for Ahkari''s trading company, protecting their goods and personnel along the dangerous roads between Dawnstar and Riften. His duties include defending against bandits, wild animals, and other threats while maintaining constant vigilance during their travels.', '* Skilled heavy armor warrior proficient with mace and shield combat techniques * Experienced guard with keen senses and tactical awareness * Adept at surviving Skyrim''s harsh environment and lengthy road journeys * Natural night vision and agility inherent to Khajiit physiology * Capable of handling multiple types of threats from bandits to dangerous wildlife', 'Kharjo speaks in the traditional third-person manner of Khajiit, with a formal yet philosophical tone that reflects both his warrior discipline and cultural background. His speech often includes practical wisdom and occasional dry humor, delivered with the distinctive Khajiit accent.', '* Repay his debt to Ahkari through loyal service * Eventually return to his homeland of Elsweyr * Protect the caravan and its members from harm * Maintain his honor and warrior''s dignity despite his circumstances * Recover from past mistakes and build a respectable future');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('khayla', 'Khayla is a skilled Khajiit warrior and stealth expert who serves as both protector and trainer within Ri''saad''s traveling merchant caravan. Her pragmatic nature and combat expertise make her an invaluable member of the nomadic trading group, while her mastery of stealth techniques has earned her recognition as a respected teacher in the art of sneaking.', 'khajiit, warrior, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_femalekhajiit', '', 'Born and raised among the trading caravans of Elsweyr, Khayla learned early the necessity of both combat and stealth for survival. She joined Ri''saad''s caravan as a young adult, having proven herself capable of protecting merchants from bandits and wildlife while maintaining the discretion necessary for dealing with Skyrim''s often-prejudiced population. Her years of experience traveling Skyrim''s harsh terrain have honed both her warrior skills and her teaching abilities.', 'Khayla exhibits a practical, survival-focused mindset tempered with genuine compassion for others, as shown by her concern for the Nordic population facing dragon attacks. She maintains a professional demeanor when training others but shows loyalty and dedication to her caravan family. Despite facing prejudice as a Khajiit in Skyrim, she remains level-headed and focused on her duties.', 'Like most Khajiit, Khayla possesses a feline appearance with fur-covered body and distinctive cat-like features. She maintains a warrior''s physique, muscular and agile, developed through years of combat and traveling. Her movements are graceful and controlled, typical of those who have mastered the art of stealth.', '* Ri''saad - Respected caravan leader and employer who trusts her combat abilities * Fellow Caravan Members - Close-knit working relationship built on mutual trust and survival * Training Students - Professional relationships with those seeking to learn stealth techniques * Local Guards - Cautious but professional interactions due to prevalent anti-Khajiit prejudice', 'Khayla serves as both a caravan guard and a trainer in the art of stealth, protecting the merchants while offering instruction to those seeking to improve their sneaking abilities. Her dual role makes her essential to both the caravan''s survival and its economic success through training fees.', '* Expert in stealth techniques and quiet movement * Accomplished warrior skilled with sword and shield combat * Proficient in light and heavy armor usage * Experienced survivor with knowledge of Skyrim''s wilderness * Capable teacher of stealth techniques', 'Khayla speaks in the traditional Khajiit third-person manner, though her warrior background leads her to be more direct and practical in her communication than many of her merchants companions. Her tone is professional and straightforward, especially when teaching.', '* Ensure the continued survival and success of Ri''saad''s caravan * Advance her reputation as a stealth trainer to attract more students * Help protect Skyrim''s settlements from dragon attacks when possible * Overcome anti-Khajiit prejudice through demonstrated competence and reliability');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kibell', 'Kibell is a seasoned Nord carriage driver stationed in Markarth who serves as both a vital transportation link and an informal historian of the Reach. His extensive knowledge of local history and current events, combined with his approachable demeanor, makes him a valuable source of information for travelers while providing safe passage through the dangerous territories of the Reach.', 'nord, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Kibell witnessed the Forsworn Uprising and Ulfric Stormcloak''s violent reclamation of Markarth firsthand. His experiences during these turbulent times, combined with years of traversing the region''s dangerous roads, have given him unique insights into the complex political and social dynamics of the area. He chose the life of a carriage driver to maintain his independence while serving his community.', 'Kibell is a friendly and talkative individual who takes pride in sharing his knowledge of local history and current events with passengers. Despite the dangers of his profession, he maintains an optimistic outlook and shows genuine concern for his passengers'' safety. He demonstrates diplomatic neutrality regarding the ongoing conflicts, though his Nord heritage occasionally colors his perspective.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the weathered features typical of someone who spends most of their time outdoors. His hands are calloused from years of handling reins, and his posture reflects the alertness required for navigating dangerous roads.', '* Other Carriage Drivers - Maintains a professional network with drivers from other holds * Markarth Guards - Cooperative relationship for ensuring traveler safety * Local Merchants - Regular business connections through traveler referrals * Forsworn - Cautious awareness and strategic avoidance * Calcelmo - Respectful acknowledgment of the scholar''s expertise on Dwemer history', 'Kibell serves as Markarth''s primary carriage driver, responsible for safely transporting passengers to various hold capitals across Skyrim. His role extends beyond mere transportation, as he acts as an unofficial ambassador for Markarth, providing valuable information and insights to travelers while ensuring their safe passage through the notoriously dangerous Reach.', '* Expert wagon handling and navigation of treacherous mountain roads * Extensive knowledge of Reach geography and safe travel routes * Proficient with an iron dagger for self-defense * Strong understanding of local history and current events * Basic survival skills necessary for long-distance travel', 'Kibell speaks in a casual, approachable manner with a slight Nordic accent, often peppering his conversation with historical facts and practical advice. His tone is informative yet friendly, making complex historical events accessible to travelers.', '* Maintain safe and reliable transportation services despite the region''s dangers * Preserve and share the history and stories of the Reach with travelers * Build a reputation as the most knowledgeable and reliable carriage driver in the region * Eventually save enough gold to expand his transportation business');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kjar', 'Kjar is a seasoned Nord ship captain who commands The North Wind, a vessel permanently moored at Windhelm''s docks. A lifetime sailor with an unwavering dedication to river life, he maintains strict authority over his ship while embodying the hardy independence characteristic of both Nord culture and maritime tradition.', 'nord, sailor, eastmarch, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised along Skyrim''s waterways, Kjar has spent his entire life as a river sailor, claiming to have been on the water since he could walk. He worked his way up from a common sailor to become captain of The North Wind, though recent events have forced his ship to remain docked at Windhelm, possibly due to increased bandit activity or economic hardships.', 'Kjar is a stern, no-nonsense captain who demands absolute loyalty from his crew and expects strict adherence to his rules. Though gruff and sometimes intimidating, he has a strong sense of justice and rewards those who prove their worth. His deep connection to river life has made him somewhat of a philosopher about freedom, though he expresses these thoughts in simple, direct terms.', 'A weathered Nord male with the robust build typical of his race, hardened by years of river work and sailing. His features bear the marks of prolonged exposure to the elements, with calloused hands and sun-weathered skin characteristic of a lifetime spent on the water.', '* The North Wind - His beloved ship, which he refers to as his ''mistress'' * Former Crew Member - Turned antagonist who betrayed him to lead a gang of thieves * Windhelm Dock Workers - Professional acquaintances who respect his authority as captain * Local Merchants - Business connections for cargo hauling operations', 'Captain of The North Wind, responsible for managing cargo operations and maintaining order on his vessel. Though currently unable to sail, he continues to maintain his ship and authority, suggesting he still conducts some form of business from his permanent berth.', '* Experienced navigator and helmsman with extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s waterways * Proficient swordsman, capable of defending his ship with a steel sword * Leadership abilities developed through years of commanding crew members * Expert knowledge of cargo handling and river trade operations', 'Speaks in a direct, authoritative manner with the gruff accent typical of Nord sailors. Uses maritime terminology and straightforward language, often making declarative statements that brook no argument.', '* Restore his ship''s active sailing status and resume regular cargo operations * Maintain order and discipline among any future crew members * Protect his reputation and authority on the Windhelm docks * Continue living the free life of a river captain, regardless of circumstances');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kjeld', 'Kjeld is a gruff and authoritative Nord innkeeper who serves as the de facto leader of the small mining settlement of Kynesgrove. A hardworking but harsh individual, he divides his time between running the Braidwood Inn and working in Steamscorch Mine while maintaining his position as the town''s unofficial spokesperson.', 'nord, innkeeper, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Kjeld established himself in Kynesgrove where he built up the Braidwood Inn from a modest establishment into a cornerstone of the community. Through his work ethic and forceful personality, he gradually assumed leadership of the town, though his tendency to seek ''variety'' in romantic partners suggests a complicated personal history that strains his marriage.', 'Kjeld is a domineering and outspoken individual who takes pride in his work ethic while holding contempt for those he considers lazy. He displays a complex character - harsh and judgmental toward most townspeople, yet showing moments of paternal care for his son. His dismissive attitude toward local superstitions and traditional Nordic beliefs reveals a practical, no-nonsense mindset.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered features typical of someone who splits their time between mining work and inn management. His hands are calloused from physical labor, and his bearing reflects the confident posture of someone used to being in charge.', '* Iddra - His wife and co-proprietor of the Braidwood Inn, though their marriage appears strained * Kjeld the Younger - His son, whom he tries to raise with Nordic values of toughness and independence * Roggi Knot-Beard - Fellow mine worker and somewhat reluctant confidant * Other Kynesgrove Residents - Generally views them as lazy and beneath him * Various Female Companions - Implied romantic interests outside his marriage', 'Kjeld serves multiple roles in Kynesgrove as both the proprietor of the Braidwood Inn and a worker at Steamscorch Mine. He acts as the unofficial leader of Kynesgrove, handling most business dealings and speaking for the town in matters of importance.', '* Experienced miner with knowledge of ore identification and extraction * Capable businessman and negotiator * Natural leadership abilities, though somewhat heavy-handed * Basic combat skills with daggers for self-defense * Knowledge of malachite ore trading and valuation', 'Kjeld speaks in a direct, often confrontational manner, using blunt language that leaves no room for misinterpretation. His speech patterns reflect his authoritative position, frequently making declarative statements rather than suggestions.', '* Maintain his position as Kynesgrove''s primary authority figure * Expand the mining operation and increase malachite ore production * Ensure his son grows up to be tough and self-reliant * Keep the town productive despite what he sees as a lazy population');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kjeld_the_younger', 'Kjeld the Younger is a brash young Nord working in his family''s mine who masks his youth and inexperience with an inflated sense of importance and tough-guy posturing. Despite his cocky exterior, he remains a child at heart, struggling to balance his desire to prove himself as a man with his actual maturity level and family obligations.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in the small settlement of Kynesgrove, Kjeld has lived a relatively privileged life as the son of the local business owners. His father''s ownership of both the Braidwood Inn and Steamscorch Mine has given him a sense of entitlement and authority from an early age. Growing up in the shadow of his father''s success, he began working in the mine as a way to prove his worth and masculinity.', 'Kjeld exhibits classic teenage bravado, constantly trying to assert his dominance and importance while hiding his insecurities. He struggles with authority, particularly when it comes to domestic responsibilities, yet shows childlike enthusiasm for activities he deems appropriately masculine like hunting. His confrontational attitude masks a deep desire for respect and recognition from both his family and the community.', 'A young Nord male in his mid-teens with the sturdy build typical of his race, though not yet fully developed into adult proportions. His body shows early signs of the muscular development common to miners, with callused hands and the occasional scrape or bruise from his work.', '* Kjeld (Father) - Complex relationship marked by both admiration and a desire to prove himself worthy * Iddra (Mother) - Frequently conflicts with her over chores and responsibilities * Sister - Shows typical sibling rivalry and reluctance to help care for her * Fellow Miners - Attempts to establish himself as an equal despite his youth * Travelers - Treats with suspicion and attempted intimidation to assert authority', 'Works as a miner in his father''s Steamscorch Mine, though his position is likely more privileged than other workers due to his family connections. Occasionally helps at the Braidwood Inn, though he considers such work beneath him and tries to avoid it when possible.', '* Basic mining techniques and ore extraction * Rudimentary combat abilities, mostly posturing rather than actual experience * Growing physical strength from mining work * Basic knowledge of inn operations, though reluctantly applied', 'Speaks with exaggerated bravado and frequent threats or boasts, often referencing his father''s authority. His speech patterns reveal his youth through occasional childish excitement or whining, especially when dealing with family members.', '* Prove himself as a legitimate authority figure in Kynesgrove despite his youth * Gain recognition as a capable miner and worker independent of his father''s influence * Avoid domestic responsibilities while pursuing more ''masculine'' activities like hunting * Eventually take over his father''s business operations and establish himself as a respected community leader');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kleppr', 'Kleppr is the long-suffering proprietor of the Silver-Blood Inn in Markarth, caught between managing a prestigious establishment and enduring a notably contentious marriage. Despite the constant domestic strife, he maintains a professional demeanor and ensures the inn remains a cornerstone of Markarth''s hospitality services.', 'nord, innkeeper, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth, Kleppr worked his way up from a simple barkeep to managing the Silver-Blood Inn, one of the city''s most prominent establishments. His marriage to Frabbi, while producing two children, has devolved into a constant battle of wills that has become notorious among Markarth''s residents. The Silver-Blood family''s ownership of the inn places additional pressure on him to maintain high standards despite his domestic troubles.', 'Kleppr exhibits a world-weary demeanor marked by passive-aggressive responses, particularly in interactions with his wife Frabbi. He attempts to maintain a professional facade when dealing with customers, though his marital disputes frequently spill into public view. Despite his circumstances, he shows dedication to his work and genuine concern for his children''s well-being.', 'A middle-aged Nord male with the weathered features typical of someone who has spent years working indoors in a busy establishment. He has the sturdy build characteristic of his race, though perhaps softened somewhat by years of innkeeper work rather than physical labor.', '* Frabbi - Wife, with whom he shares an intensely antagonistic relationship marked by constant bickering * Hroki - Daughter, whom he tries to protect from the worst of his marital strife * Hreinn - Son, who is well aware of his parents'' difficult relationship * Silver-Blood Family - Employers who own the inn * Markarth Guards - Professional relationship as they frequently patrol the inn', 'Kleppr serves as the primary manager of the Silver-Blood Inn, responsible for all aspects of its operation including serving customers, maintaining rooms, and managing inventory. He handles guest services, room rentals, and food and drink sales while ensuring the establishment maintains standards worthy of the Silver-Blood name.', '* Experienced in business management and customer service * Knowledgeable about local rumors and current events in Markarth * Proficient in food and drink preparation * Basic self-defense abilities with an iron dagger * Skilled at maintaining order in a busy inn', 'He speaks with the direct manner typical of Nords, though his tone often carries undertones of exhaustion and resignation. His speech frequently includes subtle jabs at his wife and self-deprecating remarks about his marriage.', '* Maintain the Silver-Blood Inn''s reputation as Markarth''s premier establishment * Preserve some semblance of family stability despite his troubled marriage * Ensure his children''s future success despite their difficult home environment * Eventually pass the inn management to one of his children');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('klimmek', 'Klimmek is a dedicated Nord fisherman from Ivarstead who serves as a vital supply line to the Greybeards of High Hrothgar, making regular deliveries up the treacherous 7,000 Steps despite his advancing age. He represents the everyday Nordic value of duty and perseverance, while struggling with both professional competition and matters of the heart.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Ivarstead, Klimmek has spent his entire life as a fisherman along the Treva River, learning the trade from an early age. He took on the responsibility of delivering supplies to High Hrothgar in his younger years, continuing a tradition vital to both the Greybeards and his village. His life took a complicated turn when he agreed to share his home with fellow fisherman Bassianus Axius, leading to both business and romantic tensions.', 'Klimmek is hardworking, responsible, and dedicated to his duties, though he can be somewhat passive in confrontational situations. He shows a gentle and romantic side in his pursuit of love, albeit with little success, and demonstrates patience despite his frustrations with his business partner. His sense of duty often overrides his personal discomfort, as shown by his continued deliveries to High Hrothgar despite his aging body.', 'A middle-aged Nord with the weathered features typical of someone who spends long hours outdoors. His hands are calloused from years of handling fishing nets and climbing the 7,000 Steps. His sturdy build, while still strong, shows signs of age catching up with him.', '* Bassianus Axius - Housemate and business partner with whom he has a strained relationship * Fastred - Local girl he harbors romantic feelings for, though she is involved with Bassianus * Lynly Star-Sung - The bard he attempts to court at the Vilemyr Inn, who rejects his advances * The Greybeards - Respected religious order he serves through his supply deliveries * Gwilin - Fellow townsperson he occasionally converses with', 'Klimmek works primarily as a fisherman on the Treva River, managing a small but sustainable fishing operation. He also serves as the unofficial supplier to the Greybeards, making regular deliveries of food and other necessities to High Hrothgar, a task that has become an important part of his identity in the community.', '* Experienced fisherman with extensive knowledge of local fishing spots and techniques * Skilled mountaineer capable of navigating the dangerous 7,000 Steps * Basic combat abilities with a dagger for self-defense * Knowledgeable about preservation and transportation of food supplies * Familiar with weather patterns and survival skills necessary for mountain climbing', 'Klimmek speaks in a straightforward, practical manner typical of Nordic fishermen, avoiding flowery language or excessive words. His tone often carries a hint of world-weariness, particularly when discussing his climbing duties or romantic situations.', '* Find someone to eventually take over his High Hrothgar delivery duties as he ages * Maintain his fishing business despite competition from Bassianus * Find romantic companionship, whether with Fastred or another * Continue supporting the Greybeards through his supply deliveries for as long as he is able');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('knight-paladin_gelebor', 'Knight-Paladin Gelebor is one of the last remaining uncorrupted Snow Elves and an ancient guardian of the Chantry of Auri-El, serving as a living connection to his people''s noble past. He maintains his vigil at the Darkfall Cave wayshrine, steadfastly upholding his sacred duties while grappling with the corruption of his brother and the fall of his civilization.', 'snowelf, vampire, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_gelebor', '', 'Born during the height of Snow Elf civilization, Gelebor was raised and trained within the Chantry of Auri-El, eventually rising to the prestigious rank of Knight-Paladin. He survived the devastating Falmer invasion of the Chantry, which claimed the lives of his fellow priests and paladins, and has maintained his lonely vigil for thousands of years, watching his brother''s corruption and his people''s descent into savagery.', 'Gelebor exhibits remarkable patience and dignity despite his tragic circumstances, maintaining his faith in Auri-El through millennia of solitude. He is scholarly and contemplative, yet pragmatic enough to seek outside help when needed, showing both wisdom and humility. Despite witnessing the fall of his civilization and his brother''s corruption, he maintains a courteous and composed demeanor, though carries deep sorrow for his people''s fate.', 'Gelebor possesses the distinctive features of an uncorrupted Snow Elf, with pale white skin and long silvery-white hair. His face shows noble features typical of mer races, though marked by the wisdom of ages, and his bearing remains proud and dignified despite his advanced age. He stands tall with an athletic build maintained through centuries of martial training.', '* Arch-Curate Vyrthur - His corrupted brother whom he must oppose despite their familial bond * The Betrayed (Falmer) - Former Snow Elf kin who have degenerated into twisted creatures * Auri-El - The deity he has faithfully served for thousands of years * Fellow Paladins - His fallen brothers-in-arms who perished defending the Chantry', 'As Knight-Paladin of the Chantry of Auri-El, Gelebor serves as both guardian and priest, protecting the sacred wayshrines while maintaining ancient religious traditions. He is the last remaining uncorrupted priest of his order, carrying the weight of preserving Snow Elf religious knowledge and protecting sacred artifacts.', '* Master of restoration magic and holy spells associated with Auri-El''s worship * Exceptional combat abilities honed through centuries of martial training * Extensive knowledge of Snow Elf history, religion, and ancient lore * Proficient in ancient ritual magic related to the wayshrines * Skilled in survival techniques that have allowed him to endure for millennia', 'Gelebor speaks with formal, archaic dignity reflecting his ancient origins and religious training, using precise and carefully chosen words. His tone is measured and scholarly, though tinged with subtle melancholy when discussing his people''s history.', '* Maintain his sacred duty as guardian of the wayshrines and keeper of Snow Elf religious traditions * Stop his corrupted brother and prevent further desecration of the Chantry * Preserve the truth about Snow Elf history and counter misconceptions about his people * Guide worthy seekers to Auriel''s Bow while ensuring it doesn''t fall into wrong hands');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('knjakr', 'Knjakr is a disturbed elderly Nord who lurks in the depths of Riften''s Ratway Warrens, masquerading as a kindly cook while harboring dark cannibalistic urges. Behind his warm, grandfatherly facade lies a dangerous predator who lures unsuspecting victims to his hidden cell with promises of food and shelter.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Originally trained as a cook in his younger years, Knjakr''s descent into cannibalism likely began during a harsh winter in the Rift when food was scarce and desperation led to unspeakable acts. Years of isolation in the Ratway''s depths have warped his mind, transforming what may have started as survival into a perverse obsession with consuming human flesh.', 'Knjakr maintains a carefully crafted persona of a gentle, hospitable elder to draw in potential victims, showing remarkable patience and persuasive ability. Beneath this mask lies a calculating predator who takes sadistic pleasure in the hunt, becoming openly aggressive and taunting once his true nature is revealed, suggesting a deeply fractured psyche that switches between these two distinct personalities.', 'A weathered elderly Nord with deep wrinkles and age spots across his pale skin, bearing the stooped posture common to those of advanced age. Despite his seemingly frail appearance, his hands remain strong and steady from years of cooking and wielding weapons, while his eyes retain an unnaturally sharp and predatory gleam.', '* Ratway Dwellers - Maintains cautious distance to avoid drawing attention to his activities * Thieves Guild - Likely aware of his presence but keeps their distance due to his disturbing reputation * Potential Victims - Views all visitors as possible prey, particularly travelers unlikely to be missed * Namira Cultists - Possible loose association, though he appears to operate independently', 'Ostensibly works as a cook in his hidden cell, though this is merely a front for his true activities. His real ''occupation'' involves luring, killing, and consuming unfortunate victims who wander into his domain in the Ratway Warrens.', '* Expert in food preparation and preservation techniques * Skilled in deceptive speech and manipulation * Proficient with knives both for cooking and combat * Experienced in ambush tactics and close-quarters fighting * Knowledge of human anatomy from years of butchering prey', 'Speaks in a warm, grandfatherly manner using affectionate terms like ''my darling'' and ''my sweet one'' when trying to lure victims. His speech becomes more mocking and predatory during combat, revealing his true nature through taunts and threats.', '* Continue his cannibalistic practices while maintaining his secrecy in the Ratway * Lure more unsuspecting victims to his lair * Avoid detection from authorities and other Ratway denizens * Perfect his techniques for preparing and preserving human flesh');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('knud', 'Knud is a young Nord boy living and working on his family''s farm near Solitude, representing the next generation of Skyrim''s agricultural backbone. His innocent curiosity and playful nature are balanced with early lessons in responsibility through his daily farm duties, embodying the Nordic values of hard work and family devotion.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', '', '', 'Born to farmers Katla and Snilling, Knud has spent his entire young life on their family farm near Solitude''s outskirts. Despite his father''s concerns about his reading abilities, his mother ensures he learns practical farming skills that will allow him to eventually take over the family business. His childhood is shaped by the harsh but beautiful environment of Haafingar Hold, where he balances farm work with imaginative play.', 'Knud exhibits the natural curiosity and enthusiasm typical of children his age, often engaging in imaginative play between his chores. He shows a strong sense of duty and politeness instilled by his parents, particularly toward guests. While sometimes playfully destructive in his games, he generally tries to be mindful of the farm''s needs, showing early signs of responsibility despite his youth.', 'A typical Nord child with the characteristic sturdy build of his race, though still showing the gangly nature of youth. His frequent outdoor work has given him a healthy, weathered complexion despite his young age. He moves with the boundless energy characteristic of children.', '* Katla - His mother, who encourages his farming abilities and shows patience with his playful nature * Snilling - His father, who worries about his academic abilities but accepts his farming destiny * Farm Animals - Particularly close to the goats he helps tend * Local Guards - Objects of fascination, as he often pretends to be a soldier', 'As a child farmhand, Knud assists with various age-appropriate tasks around his family''s farm, with a particular focus on tending to the goats. His work schedule is structured but allows for breaks and play time, teaching him the balance of responsibility and leisure that farm life requires.', '* Basic animal husbandry, particularly with goats * Fundamental farming techniques appropriate for his age * Creative play and improvisation, especially in military role-playing * Basic physical labor and farm maintenance tasks', 'Knud speaks with the characteristic directness of a child, using simple language and showing enthusiasm in his interactions. His dialogue reflects both his youth and proper Nordic upbringing, always addressing adults with respect and proper titles.', '* Learn all aspects of farming to eventually take over the family farm * Become strong like the soldiers he admires * Make his parents proud through hard work and dedication * Master the skills needed for successful farm management');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kodlak_whitemane', 'Kodlak Whitemane serves as the wise and respected Harbinger of the Companions, leading Skyrim''s most renowned warrior guild from their hall of Jorrvaskr in Whiterun. A philosophical warrior-sage who values honor above all else, he struggles with his lycanthropy while seeking to guide the Companions along a noble path and secure his own passage to Sovngarde.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, companions', '', '', 'sk_kodlakwhitemane', '', 'Born into a Nord family, Kodlak lost his parents at a young age and spent his youth traveling Tamriel as a wandering warrior, honing his combat skills. He was discovered in Hammerfell by the previous Harbinger Askar while serving as a bodyguard, who recognized his potential and brought him back to join the Companions, where he eventually rose to become their leader and joined the secretive Circle.', 'Kodlak is a deeply thoughtful and introspective individual who carefully weighs the consequences of his actions and decisions. He maintains a stoic demeanor befitting a Nordic warrior while displaying wisdom and philosophical insight that makes him more than just a simple fighter. Though proud of the Companions'' traditions, he questions certain aspects like the Circle''s lycanthropy, showing his willingness to challenge established practices when they conflict with his principles.', 'An elderly but still-powerful Nord warrior with a strong physical presence despite his advanced age. His face bears the weathered features of a lifetime of combat, with distinctive white hair and beard that earned him his surname. His eyes carry both the sharp focus of a veteran fighter and the contemplative gaze of a philosopher.', '* The Circle - Close confidants and inner council of the Companions * Vilkas and Farkas - Views them as sons, having helped raise and train them * Jergen - Former Companion who brought the twins to Jorrvaskr * Askar - Previous Harbinger who recruited him * The Silver Hand - Sworn enemies who hunt werewolves', 'As Harbinger of the Companions, Kodlak serves as their spiritual leader and chief advisor, though he holds no formal authority over them in keeping with their traditions. He manages the organization''s affairs, guides new members, and maintains their reputation while upholding their principles of honor and glory in battle.', '* Master-level warrior specializing in one-handed weapons and heavy armor * Exceptional tactical knowledge and battlefield leadership abilities * Experienced werewolf with full control over his beast form * Diplomatic and administrative skills from years of leading the Companions * Deep understanding of Nordic traditions and warrior culture', 'Speaks with formal, measured tones that reflect both his Nordic warrior heritage and his philosophical nature. His words carry the weight of wisdom and experience, often incorporating metaphors and references to honor and tradition.', '* Cure himself of lycanthropy to ensure his soul reaches Sovngarde * Maintain the Companions'' honor and keep them on a noble path * Guide the next generation of warriors to uphold their ancient traditions * Protect the Companions from both external threats and internal corruption');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kodrir', 'Kodrir is a bitter and hostile Nord lumberjack working at Anga''s Mill, known for his extreme distrust of strangers and perpetual discontent with his work situation. His aggressive demeanor and antagonistic relationships with his coworkers hint at a deeper history of personal grievances and possible connection to criminal elements, particularly given his unexplored animosity toward the former mill worker Ennodius.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally from somewhere in Skyrim''s northern holds, Kodrir found work at Anga''s Mill after a troubled past that left him deeply distrustful of outsiders. His particular hatred for the Imperial worker Ennodius and the existence of a special bottle of skooma tied to an unfinished quest suggests possible involvement with drug trafficking or other criminal activities that were never fully revealed in the game.', 'Kodrir is aggressive, antisocial, and perpetually disgruntled, showing open hostility to strangers and constant dissatisfaction with his work conditions. His defensive reactions and quick temper suggest someone hiding dark secrets or past trauma, while his conflicts with coworkers reveal an inability or unwillingness to maintain positive social relationships.', 'A weathered Nord male with the muscular build typical of someone who performs heavy physical labor. His face likely bears the harsh lines and weathering common to those who work outdoors in Skyrim''s brutal climate, with the calloused hands and strong arms of an experienced lumberjack.', '* Aeri - Employer whom he openly resents and feels underappreciated by * Leifur - Coworker who frequently mocks his attitude and lack of faith * Ennodius Papius - Former Imperial coworker whom he deeply despised and may have wished dead * The Divines - Shows clear disdain for religion, particularly Lady Mara', 'Kodrir works as a lumberjack at Anga''s Mill, performing physically demanding tasks like chopping wood, sharpening axes, and carrying water for twelve hours each day. Despite the stable employment, he shows constant dissatisfaction with his position and appears to view it as beneath him.', '* Experienced woodcutter with expertise in handling axes and lumber * Physical strength and endurance from years of manual labor * Possible experience with skooma trafficking or illegal trade * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense', 'Kodrir speaks in a gruff, hostile manner with frequent use of threats and dismissive commands. His vocabulary and tone reflect his antagonistic nature, often telling others to ''get lost'' or ''watch their mouth'' when addressing him.', '* Maintain distance from others to protect his secrets and past * Possibly escape his current life of manual labor at the mill * May seek revenge or resolution regarding the mysterious situation with Ennodius * Avoid scrutiny from authorities regarding potential criminal connections');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kolbjorn_guard', 'A dedicated Nord guard stationed at Kolbjorn Barrow who met a tragic end during the excavation of the ancient Nordic ruins. He served as part of an elite unit tasked with protecting the archaeological expedition, displaying unwavering commitment to his duties until his final moments.', 'nord, guard, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Raven Rock, this Nord guard grew up during the difficult period when the ebony mines were failing. He chose to join the Redoran Guard to help maintain order and protect his hometown, eventually being selected for the specialized detail at Kolbjorn Barrow due to his experience with Nordic ruins and dedication to duty.', 'Stoic and disciplined, the Kolbjorn Guard approached his duties with utmost seriousness and professionalism. He harbored a deep respect for Nordic history and traditions, while maintaining a practical mindset that kept him focused on the safety of those under his protection rather than the allure of ancient treasures.', 'A sturdy Nord male with weathered features typical of those who spend their days patrolling in harsh conditions. His muscular build and battle-hardened physique reflect years of guard service, while his face bears the distinct scars of previous encounters with ash spawn and other Solstheim threats.', '* Ralis Sedarys - Employer and expedition leader he was assigned to protect * Captain Veleth - Direct superior officer in the Redoran Guard chain of command * Fellow Kolbjorn Guards - Close-knit unit who shared dangerous duties at the barrow * Second Councilor Arano - Authority figure who authorized the guard detail', 'Served as a specialized guard in the Redoran Guard force, specifically assigned to protect the archaeological expedition at Kolbjorn Barrow. His role combined traditional guard duties with the specialized task of securing an active excavation site against both mundane and supernatural threats.', '* Proficient in traditional Nordic combat techniques with sword and shield * Experienced in dealing with draugr and other undead threats common to Nordic ruins * Well-versed in Redoran Guard protocols and procedures * Basic knowledge of ancient Nordic burial customs and their associated dangers', 'Speaks in a gruff, authoritative tone typical of Nord guards, favoring direct commands and concise reports. His vocabulary reflects both his guard training and familiarity with Nordic customs, often using terms related to both Dunmer and Nordic culture.', '* Maintain the security and integrity of the Kolbjorn Barrow excavation site * Protect the archaeological team from the dangers lurking within the ruins * Uphold the reputation of the Redoran Guard through exemplary service * Earn enough money to eventually retire comfortably in Raven Rock');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('korir', 'Korir is the embittered Jarl of Winterhold, presiding over a once-great city reduced to ruins after the Great Collapse. A proud Nord traditionalist, he harbors deep resentment toward the College of Winterhold and its mages, whom he blames for his hold''s devastating decline, while struggling to maintain his authority and restore his city''s former glory.', 'nord, noble, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into Winterhold''s nobility, Korir ascended to the position of Jarl following the Great Collapse that destroyed most of the city in 4E 122. Having witnessed his hold''s transformation from a seat of power to a mere shadow of its former self, he grew increasingly distrustful of magic and those who practice it. His political alignment with the Stormcloaks stems from both Nord traditionalism and a desire to preserve what little remains of Winterhold''s sovereignty.', 'Korir is a bitter, suspicious, and deeply prejudiced man, particularly against mages and elves whom he holds responsible for Winterhold''s destruction. His personality is dominated by a combination of pride in Winterhold''s past glory and shame at its current state, making him defensive and often hostile toward outsiders. Despite his flaws, he shows genuine care for his hold''s remaining citizens and maintains a strong sense of duty to his position.', 'A middle-aged Nord with the sturdy build typical of his race, bearing the weathered features of one who has endured Winterhold''s harsh climate. His face shows the strain of his position and bitter disposition, with stern eyes and a perpetual frown marking his otherwise noble countenance.', '* Thaena - His wife and staunch supporter who shares his prejudices against the College * Assur - His young son and heir to the Jarldom of Winterhold * College of Winterhold - Deeply distrusted institution he believes responsible for the Great Collapse * Other Jarls - Strained relationships due to Winterhold''s diminished status * Kraldar - Political rival who replaces him if Imperials take control * Stormcloaks - Allied faction he supports in the Civil War', 'As Jarl of Winterhold, Korir serves as the political and administrative leader of the hold, though his authority is largely symbolic given the city''s diminished state. He maintains his court in the Jarl''s Longhouse, handling what little governance remains necessary in the sparsely populated hold while attempting to rebuild Winterhold''s reputation among the other holds.', '* Basic combat abilities expected of a Nord nobleman * Administrative and leadership capabilities, though limited by circumstances * Knowledge of Nordic history and traditions * Political acumen, albeit hampered by his prejudices * Survival skills necessary for living in Winterhold''s harsh climate', 'Korir speaks with the authority expected of a Jarl, though his tone often carries underlying bitterness and resentment. His speech frequently includes references to Winterhold''s former glory and pointed criticism of the College, reflecting his preoccupation with the past and his prejudices.', '* Restore Winterhold to its former glory and status as a major hold capital * Prove the College''s culpability in the Great Collapse * Gain greater respect and recognition from other Jarls * Preserve Nordic traditions and culture in Winterhold * Maintain his position of authority despite the hold''s declined state');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kornalus', 'Kornalus is a reclusive High Elf warlock who has claimed the ruins of Harmugstahl as his laboratory for conducting twisted experiments on frostbite spiders. His obsessive pursuit of magical knowledge and complete disregard for ethics has led him to become a dangerous hermit researcher, attempting to unlock the secrets of controlling and enhancing arachnid specimens through dark magical practices.', 'highelf, mage, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, Kornalus was expelled for conducting forbidden experiments on living subjects. He retreated to the isolated fort of Harmugstahl, where he could continue his research without interference from ethical oversight or concerned colleagues. His years of solitude and exposure to dark magics have gradually eroded his grip on sanity.', 'Kornalus is a highly intelligent but mentally unstable researcher who shows complete disregard for ethical boundaries or the suffering of others. His obsession with spider-based experimentation has consumed his life, leading to paranoid and aggressive behavior towards any perceived threats to his work. He demonstrates classic signs of magical addiction and isolation-induced psychosis.', 'Tall and gaunt even by Altmer standards, Kornalus bears the pallid complexion of one who rarely sees sunlight. His angular features are made more severe by dark circles under his eyes and slight magical burns on his hands from failed experiments. His once-pristine appearance has deteriorated from years of neglecting personal care in favor of his research.', '* Frostbite Spiders - His experimental subjects and closest companions, though they often prove difficult to control * College of Winterhold - Former association ended in exile due to ethical violations * Local Bandits - Occasional hostile encounters with groups attempting to claim his fort * Traveling merchants - Viewed as potential sources for supplies and unwitting test subjects', 'Kornalus serves as a self-appointed magical researcher and spider experimentalist, operating without oversight or ethical constraints. His work combines elements of conjuration, alteration, and alchemy in attempts to create enhanced and controlled spider specimens.', '* Master-level knowledge of Conjuration magic, particularly focusing on creature control * Advanced understanding of alchemical principles and poison creation * Expertise in spider anatomy and behavior modification * Proficient in defensive magic and ward casting * Capable of creating complex magical apparatus for experiments', 'Kornalus speaks with the refined accent typical of Altmer nobility, though his speech often devolves into manic rambling when discussing his research. His vocabulary is highly technical and academic, frequently punctuated by frustrated outbursts when describing failed experiments.', '* Perfect the art of controlling and enhancing frostbite spiders through magical means * Create a superior breed of spiders that fully bend to his will * Prove the validity of his research to those who doubted and expelled him * Expand his influence beyond Harmugstahl once his spider army is perfected');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kottir_red-shoal', 'Kottir Red-Shoal is a hardened Nord commander who leads the Stormcloak forces in the Reach with unwavering dedication to Ulfric''s cause. A passionate nationalist and skilled military leader, he embodies the Stormcloaks'' drive to liberate Skyrim from Imperial control and restore the worship of Talos.', 'nord, warrior, reach, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh environment, Kottir likely came from a traditional Nord family that maintained strong ties to their ancestral beliefs and customs. His martial prowess and leadership abilities caught Ulfric''s attention early in the rebellion, leading to his appointment as commander of the strategic Reach campaign.', 'Kottir is a fierce nationalist who displays unwavering loyalty to Ulfric Stormcloak and deep contempt for those he views as traitors to Skyrim. He exhibits the typical Nord traits of directness and martial pride, combined with a strategic mind that makes him an effective military commander. His passionate hatred for the Thalmor and Imperial sympathizers drives his every action.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered features typical of a seasoned soldier who has spent considerable time in military camps. His body bears the scars and muscular build of someone who has dedicated their life to warfare and survival in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Supreme commander and object of intense loyalty * Galmar Stone-Fist - Superior officer and strategic coordinator * Raerek - Rival administrator in Markarth (when city is under Imperial control) * Local Reachmen - Tense relationship due to territorial conflicts * Fellow Stormcloak Officers - Maintains professional military camaraderie', 'Commander of the Reach Stormcloak Camp, responsible for coordinating military operations against Imperial forces in the region. Upon successful capture of Markarth, he serves as the military administrator within Understone Keep, overseeing Stormcloak control of the city.', '* Expert in tactical warfare and military strategy * Proficient with both one-handed and two-handed weapons * Skilled archer and marksman * Experienced in wilderness survival and camp management * Natural leader with strong command abilities', 'Speaks with the direct, passionate manner typical of Nord warriors, often using martial metaphors and references to honor and tradition. His tone carries the authority of a military commander while maintaining the familiar camaraderie common among Stormcloak officers.', '* Secure the Reach for the Stormcloak cause and eliminate Imperial presence * Restore proper Nord rule to Markarth and the surrounding holds * Drive out Thalmor influence from Skyrim * Support Ulfric''s claim as the true High King * Preserve and protect Nord traditions and the worship of Talos');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('krag', 'Krag was a reclusive Breton conjurer who chose to live in isolation within the ancient Dwemer ruins of Nchuand-Zel, dedicating himself to the study of dark arts and conjuration magic. His mysterious presence in these dangerous ruins and eventual death speak to both his dedication to forbidden knowledge and the ultimately fatal price of his obsession.', 'breton, mage, reach', '', '', 'sk_malewarlock', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, Krag grew disillusioned with the restrictions placed on magical research and sought isolation to pursue darker forms of conjuration. He discovered the ruins of Nchuand-Zel and established a makeshift research space, living among the dangerous Dwemer constructs and hostile creatures while conducting his arcane experiments.', 'Krag was a deeply introspective and obsessive individual, willing to risk everything in pursuit of magical knowledge. His self-imposed exile and dedication to dangerous research suggest both a misanthropic streak and an unshakeable determination. His journal entries reveal a methodical mind prone to detailed observation and analysis, though possibly touched by the madness that often afflicts those who delve too deeply into dark magic.', 'A middle-aged Breton male with the characteristic slight build of his race, likely gaunt from his isolated lifestyle and magical exertions. His hands would have shown the typical calluses and minor burns common to practicing mages, while his face likely bore the premature aging often seen in those who dabble in dark magic.', '* College of Winterhold - Former association, likely strained or severed * Local Markarth Guards - Avoided contact, viewed as a potential threat * Dwemer Automatons - Subjects of study and constant threats * Fellow Mages - Deliberately distanced himself from the magical community', 'Independent magical researcher and conjurer operating outside official institutions or oversight. His self-appointed role involved studying Dwemer ruins while pursuing advances in conjuration magic, supporting himself through enchanting and possibly selling magical discoveries to discrete buyers.', '* Master-level conjuration magic with focus on summoning Daedric entities * Experienced in survival within Dwemer ruins * Knowledgeable in Dwemer archaeology and artifacts * Proficient in enchanting and alchemy * Basic combat magic for self-defense against ruins'' dangers', 'Formal and academic in his writing, with a tendency toward precise, technical language when discussing magical theory. His isolation likely led to somewhat stilted and archaic speech patterns when dealing with others.', '* Unlock the secrets of advanced conjuration magic beyond institutional limitations * Document and understand the connection between Dwemer technology and magical theory * Achieve breakthrough discoveries in combining Dwemer mechanical principles with conjuration * Prove the validity of his unconventional magical research methods');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kraldar', 'Kraldar is a progressive-minded Nord noble in Winterhold who becomes Jarl under Imperial control, notable for his unique positive stance toward the College of Winterhold. Unlike most locals, he maintains diplomatic relations with the mages and envisions restoring Winterhold to its former glory through cooperation rather than suspicion.', 'nord, noble, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into one of Winterhold''s few remaining noble families, Kraldar witnessed the city''s decline following the Great Collapse but refused to blame the College. He cultivated relationships with the mages, particularly claiming friendship with Arch-Mage Savos Aren, though the extent of this connection remains unclear. His moderate views and support of Imperial governance eventually positioned him as the Empire''s choice for Jarl.', 'Kraldar is diplomatic, forward-thinking, and optimistic about Winterhold''s future despite its current state. He shows unusual tolerance toward magic users for a Nord, preferring cooperation over conflict. His personality combines traditional Nordic pride in Winterhold''s history with a pragmatic approach to rebuilding through alliance with the College.', 'A mature Nord male with the weathered features typical of Winterhold''s harsh climate. His bearing reflects his noble background despite his modest circumstances, carrying himself with dignity and purpose. He shows signs of age but maintains a robust Nordic physique.', '* Thonjolf - Loyal servant who follows him in exile if Winterhold falls * Savos Aren - Claims close friendship with the Arch-Mage, though this may be overstated * Korir - Political rival and predecessor as Jarl * College of Winterhold - Maintains positive diplomatic relations with the institution * Imperial Legion - Loyal supporter who serves as their chosen Jarl', 'Initially a nobleman of diminished means living in his private home, Kraldar becomes Jarl of Winterhold if the Imperial Legion takes control. In this role, he administers one of Skyrim''s most diminished holds, focusing on rebuilding relations with the College and restoring the city''s former prominence.', '* Basic combat abilities with traditional Nordic weapons, particularly the iron dagger * Administrative and diplomatic capabilities as befitting a noble and potential Jarl * Political acumen shown through navigation of Winterhold''s complex relationship with the College * Knowledge of Winterhold''s history and governance traditions', 'Speaks with the refined manner of a noble, emphasizing diplomacy and optimism. His dialogue frequently references Winterhold''s grand history and potential for restoration, showing both pride and hope.', '* Restore Winterhold to its former glory as a capital city of Skyrim * Rebuild positive relations between the town and the College of Winterhold * Secure Imperial support for Winterhold''s reconstruction * Modernize Winterhold''s approach to magic and education');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('krev_the_skinner', 'Krev the Skinner is the ruthless and fanatical leader of the Silver Hand, a militant organization dedicated to eradicating werewolves from Skyrim. Known for brutal interrogation methods and a particular hatred of lycanthropes, Krev has transformed the Silver Hand from a loose collection of hunters into an organized force that actively challenges the Companions of Whiterun.', 'warrior, companions', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a common bounty hunter who lost family members to werewolf attacks, Krev rose through the ranks of the Silver Hand through a combination of tactical brilliance and uncompromising brutality. After witnessing the devastation caused by lycanthropes firsthand, Krev united scattered werewolf hunters under the Silver Hand banner and established their headquarters at Gallows Rock, where they began conducting systematic operations against suspected werewolves and their sympathizers.', 'Cold, calculating, and driven by an obsessive hatred of werewolves, Krev demonstrates sociopathic tendencies in the pursuit of perceived justice. Shows no mercy to captured lycanthropes or their associates, earning the nickname ''the Skinner'' through notorious interrogation methods. Despite this brutality, maintains a disciplined and organized approach to leadership, inspiring fierce loyalty among Silver Hand followers.', 'A weathered Nord of imposing stature, with numerous battle scars across face and body from years of hunting dangerous prey. Muscular build developed through constant combat, with calloused hands and sharp, predatory eyes that constantly scan for threats.', '* Silver Hand Members - Loyal followers who view Krev as a legendary werewolf hunter * The Companions - Bitter enemies, particularly their inner circle * Vigilants of Stendarr - Occasional allies in the fight against supernatural threats * Local Nord Villages - Information network for werewolf sightings and suspicious activity', 'Serves as the supreme commander of the Silver Hand, coordinating werewolf hunting operations across Skyrim from their fortress at Gallows Rock. Personally leads high-priority missions and oversees the training of new recruits in specialized anti-lycanthrope combat techniques.', '* Master-level skill in both one-handed and two-handed combat, specializing in silver weapons * Expert tracker with extensive knowledge of werewolf behavior and weaknesses * Accomplished interrogator and torture specialist * Strategic military commander with expertise in guerrilla warfare tactics * Proficient alchemist focusing on poisons effective against lycanthropes', 'Speaks with cold authority and barely contained contempt, often using dehumanizing terms when referring to werewolves and their allies. Favors direct, threatening statements punctuated by dark promises of what awaits those who harbor lycanthropes.', '* Eliminate all werewolves from Skyrim, particularly the Circle of the Companions * Expand the Silver Hand''s influence and establish additional strongholds across Tamriel * Expose and eliminate werewolf sympathizers in positions of power * Develop more effective methods for detecting and destroying lycanthropes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kust', 'Kust is a solemn Nord priest who serves as the primary caretaker of Falkreath''s massive graveyard, the largest burial ground in all of Skyrim. His role as assistant to Runil and guardian of the dead reflects a deep spiritual connection to Arkay and an unwavering commitment to protecting the sanctity of the deceased.', 'nord, priest, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath, Kust witnessed countless burials in his hometown''s famous graveyard, which likely influenced his eventual calling to the priesthood of Arkay. His stern devotion to protecting the dead suggests possible personal losses in his past, perhaps during his younger years or during military service, though he keeps such matters private. The wars and conflicts he''s witnessed throughout his life have left him with a cynical view of human nature, yet he maintains his dedication to honoring the dead.', 'Kust is an introspective and taciturn individual who values solitude and contemplation among the tombstones he tends. His seemingly gruff exterior masks a deeply spiritual nature, though he maintains a pragmatic and sometimes cynical worldview, believing that men are neither good nor bad - just men. He shows little patience for those who disrespect the graves under his care and can be confrontational when defending the sanctity of his charge.', 'A weathered Nord of middle age, Kust bears the sturdy build typical of his race, though years of graveyard work have left him with a slightly stooped posture. His face shows the lines of someone who spends long hours in contemplation, with stern features that rarely soften into a smile.', '* Runil - His superior at the Hall of the Dead, whom he respects but maintains professional distance from * Lod - Suspicious of the blacksmith''s activities near the graveyard * Falkreath Citizens - Maintains formal but distant relationships with townsfolk * The Dead - Considers himself a guardian and caretaker to those laid to rest in his graveyard', 'As assistant priest at Falkreath''s Hall of the Dead, Kust serves as the primary caretaker and guardian of Skyrim''s largest graveyard. His duties include maintaining the graves, assisting with funeral rites, and ensuring the sanctity of the burial grounds is preserved. He divides his time between active graveyard maintenance and vigilant observation of the grounds.', '* Proficient in basic combat techniques for defending the graveyard * Knowledge of burial rites and customs associated with various Nordic traditions * Experienced in graveyard maintenance and tomb preservation * Basic understanding of Arkay''s rites and religious ceremonies', 'Kust speaks in short, direct sentences, often with a grave tone that matches his profession. His words carry weight and warning, particularly when addressing strangers or those he suspects might disrespect the dead.', '* Maintain and protect the sanctity of Falkreath''s graveyard * Preserve the memories and dignity of those buried under his watch * Keep unwanted elements and disrespectful visitors away from the burial grounds * Uphold the traditions and rites of Arkay in Falkreath');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kuvar', 'Kuvar is a proud Nord blacksmith and master trainer in Heavy Armor who resides near Thirsk Mead Hall on Solstheim after being driven out by Rieklings. Despite their current exile, he remains a steadfast supporter of reclaiming their ancestral mead hall and maintaining Nord warrior traditions.', 'nord, blacksmith, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Originally from Thirsk Mead Hall, Kuvar established himself as both a skilled blacksmith and an expert in heavy armor combat. He married Bujold and lived prosperously until their community grew complacent, leading to their eventual defeat and exile when Rieklings invaded their home in overwhelming numbers.', 'Kuvar is a determined and outspoken individual who isn''t afraid to voice his opinions about the need to reclaim Thirsk. He maintains a strong sense of Nord pride and warrior tradition despite their current circumstances, often pushing others to be better and stronger. Though practical enough to adapt to their exile, he harbors deep shame about their defeat and yearns to restore their former glory.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the muscular build typical of both a blacksmith and warrior. His body bears the scars and calluses of both forge work and combat, with particularly well-developed upper body strength from years of smithing.', '* Bujold - His wife and current leader of the displaced Thirsk warriors * Thirsk Warriors - Fellow displaced companions he tries to motivate and encourage * Rieklings - Enemies who drove him and his people from their home * Local Skaal - Distant cultural relatives, though he considers their beliefs nonsense', 'Kuvar serves as both the community''s blacksmith and a master trainer in Heavy Armor. He maintains the group''s weapons and armor while also providing expert instruction to those seeking to master heavy armor combat techniques.', '* Master-level knowledge and training ability in Heavy Armor combat techniques * Expert-level blacksmithing abilities * Proficient warrior skilled with Nordic weapons * Survival skills necessary for life in Solstheim''s harsh environment', 'Speaks directly and honestly with a strong Nordic accent, often using practical metaphors related to smithing or combat. His tone carries both pride in their traditions and frustration at their current situation.', '* Retake Thirsk Mead Hall from the Rieklings * Restore the warrior tradition and former glory of Thirsk * Strengthen and motivate his fellow warriors to overcome their current weakness * Maintain Nord traditions and prove worthy of their ancestral home');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kvenel_the_tongue', 'Kvenel the Tongue was a legendary Nord warrior renowned for his mastery of the Thu''um and exceptional combat prowess during the Merethic Era. Now existing as a powerful draugr lord, he guards his burial chamber in Volunruud with the same fierce determination that marked his mortal life, wielding both ancient Nordic weapons and the power of his Voice.', 'nord', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born during the Merethic Era, Kvenel earned his epithet ''the Tongue'' through his exceptional mastery of the Voice, studying under the ancient Dragons before their downfall. He served as a prominent warrior-chief among the ancient Nords, leading successful campaigns against their enemies and earning his place among the legendary heroes of his time. After death, his remains were interred in Volunruud with great ceremony, though like many powerful Nord warriors, his spirit remained to guard his treasured possessions.', 'Even in death, Kvenel maintains the fierce pride and warrior''s spirit that defined him in life. He embodies the ancient Nordic values of strength, honor, and combat prowess, showing no mercy to those who would disturb his rest. His ghostly presence radiates an aura of authority and power that reflects his status as a leader in life.', 'In his spectral form, Kvenel appears as a towering Nord warrior with the commanding presence befitting a warrior-chief of the Merethic Era. His ethereal form maintains the broad-shouldered, muscular build typical of Nord warriors, with sharp, angular facial features and long hair that marks him as a noble of his time.', '* Ancient Dragons - Former teachers who instructed him in the Way of the Voice * Ancient Nord Warriors - Led them in battle as their chief and commander * Modern Adventurers - Views them as trespassers to be eliminated * Other Draugr - Commands them within his burial chamber', 'In life, Kvenel served as a warrior-chief and master of the Voice, leading his people in battle and governance. In death, he continues his eternal vigil as a guardian of his burial chamber, protecting the ancient artifacts and weapons entrusted to his care.', '* Master of the Thu''um, capable of using multiple Shouts with devastating effect * Expert dual-wielding warrior, particularly skilled with ancient Nordic weapons * Natural leader with tactical combat expertise * Powerful necromantic energy that sustains his undead form * Command over lesser draugr within his domain', 'Speaks in the ancient Nordic tongue when using the Thu''um, his voice carrying the weight of centuries and the power of the dragons who taught him. In combat, he primarily communicates through battle cries and Shouts, maintaining the commanding presence he held in life.', '* Protect his burial chamber and the ancient artifacts within from all intruders * Maintain his eternal vigil as guardian of Volunruud * Preserve the honor and traditions of ancient Nordic warrior culture through his continued presence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kyr', 'Kyr was a pragmatic Nord bandit leader who operated out of Frostmere Crypt, leading a struggling band of raiders during lean times. His discovery of an ancient sword in a mysterious underground forest briefly elevated his fortunes, only to ultimately lead to his demise through betrayal and violence.', 'nord, thief, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally operating as a bandit leader in Hjaalmarch, Kyr maintained a small group that struggled due to limited raiding opportunities in the region. His fortunes improved temporarily when new recruits Eisa Blackthorn and Ra''jirr joined, leading to the discovery of valuable treasures within Frostmere Crypt, including a mysterious sword found in an underground forest.', 'Kyr exhibited the practical mindset of a survival-focused bandit leader, showing both resourcefulness in tough times and the ability to recognize opportunity when it presented itself. While capable of violence, he demonstrated leadership qualities by maintaining group cohesion during difficult periods and delegating responsibilities effectively, such as putting Eisa in charge of excavation efforts.', 'A hardy Nord male with the weathered features typical of someone who lives a rough life in Skyrim''s harsh climate. His physical form shows the marks of a life of combat and outdoor living, with a sturdy build suited to the demanding lifestyle of a bandit chief.', '* Eisa Blackthorn - Initially trusted recruit who he later suspected of betrayal * Ra''jirr - Treacherous new recruit who ultimately betrayed and mortally wounded him * Bandit Group - Leader of a small band of raiders operating from Frostmere Crypt * The Pale Lady - Mysterious entity connected to the sword he discovered, indirectly leading to his doom', 'Kyr served as the leader of a bandit group operating out of Frostmere Crypt, organizing raids on passing caravans and managing the day-to-day survival of his band. He later expanded into treasure hunting within the crypt itself, supervising excavation efforts that led to significant discoveries.', '* Capable leader with experience managing a bandit operation * Combat proficiency typical of a Nord warrior and bandit chief * Basic archaeological knowledge gained from crypt exploration * Survival skills necessary for living in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness', 'In his final moments, Kyr speaks in a raspy, labored voice punctuated by gasps and coughs, reflecting his mortal wounds. His manner of speech suggests someone used to giving orders and speaking with authority, even when severely wounded.', '* Maintain and expand his bandit operation to ensure group survival * Recover the stolen sword from Ra''jirr * Explore and exploit the resources of Frostmere Crypt * Exact revenge on those who betrayed him');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('laelette_the_vampire', 'Laelette is a tragic figure who transformed from a loving mother and wife in Morthal into a mentally unstable vampire under Alva''s influence. Her descent into darkness culminated in the murder of an innocent family and a twisted obsession with their deceased child Helgi, revealing the horrific psychological toll of vampirism on her once-human nature.', 'breton, hjaalmarch, stormcloak, vampire', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Originally a devoted wife to Thonnir and mother to Virkmund in Morthal, Laelette''s life changed dramatically when she encountered Alva, who turned her into a vampire and made her a handmaiden. Under Alva''s orders, she committed terrible acts including burning Hroggar''s family alive, though her failed attempt to turn young Helgi into a vampire particularly haunts her existence.', 'Laelette''s transformation into a vampire has completely warped her once-nurturing personality into something unhinged and obsessive. She displays signs of severe mental instability, fixating on Helgi as a potential vampire companion while seemingly disconnected from her former maternal bond with her own son. Her actions suggest both a desperate loneliness and a complete moral deterioration typical of newly-turned vampires who haven''t learned to control their darker impulses.', 'As a Breton vampire, Laelette possesses the characteristic pale, gaunt features and glowing eyes of the undead. Her once-healthy complexion has become deathly white, with dark hollows under her eyes and pronounced fangs visible when she speaks.', '* Thonnir - Abandoned husband who believes she left to join the Stormcloaks * Virkmund - Deserted son who still hopes for her return * Alva - Vampire master who turned her and controls her actions * Helgi - Deceased child she obsessively fixates on * Hroggar''s Family - Victims of her vampire-induced violence', 'Laelette serves as a vampire handmaiden to Alva, having abandoned her former life as a wife and mother. Her duties likely involve serving her vampire master''s needs while helping maintain the facade of normalcy in Morthal.', '* Proficient in destruction magic, particularly fire-based spells as evidenced by her burning of Hroggar''s house * Enhanced vampire abilities including supernatural strength and speed * Stealth capabilities typical of vampires * Basic combat abilities gained after turning', 'Her speech patterns are erratic and disturbed, often fixating on Helgi and showing signs of her deteriorated mental state. She frequently shifts between lucid moments of her former self and darker, more predatory vampiric tendencies.', '* Bring Helgi back as a vampire companion to ease her lonely existence * Serve her vampire master Alva''s commands * Potentially reconnect with her son Virkmund, though her vampiric nature prevents this * Find acceptance and companionship in her new undead state');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('laila_law-giver', 'Laila Law-Giver is the Jarl of Riften who maintains a facade of control while being largely oblivious to the corruption plaguing her city. Despite her noble intentions and dedication to her people, she is effectively a puppet ruler manipulated by Maven Black-Briar and the Thieves Guild through her corrupt advisors.', 'nord, noble, rift, legion', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born into Nord nobility, Laila inherited the position of Jarl of Riften and has ruled The Rift for many years. Her reign has been marked by a gradual decline in actual authority as the Thieves Guild and Maven Black-Briar''s influence grew, though she remains unaware of the true extent of corruption in her court. She raised two sons alone, suggesting either widowhood or an absent spouse, though the details of her personal history remain largely unknown.', 'Laila exhibits a curious mixture of noble intentions and naive trust in her corrupted advisers. She genuinely believes she maintains control over Riften while being completely unaware of the extent of criminal influence in her city. Though publicly supportive of the Stormcloaks, she privately harbors doubts about Ulfric''s leadership, showing a capacity for independent thought despite her general gullibility.', 'A mature Nord woman with the regal bearing expected of a Jarl, though perhaps softer than most Nord rulers due to her sheltered life. She maintains a dignified appearance befitting her station, with features that suggest both nobility and the weathering of age.', '* Anuriel - Her steward, secretly a Thieves Guild plant who manipulates her decisions * Maven Black-Briar - Powerful businesswoman who secretly controls much of Riften * Harrald - Her elder son who shares her political views * Saerlund - Her younger son whom she believes is mentally ill due to his anti-Stormcloak views * Unmid Snow-Shod - Her loyal housecarl and strong Stormcloak supporter * Wylandriah - Her court wizard whom she tasks with ''curing'' her son''s supposed illness', 'As Jarl of Riften, Laila Law-Giver is the official ruler of The Rift, responsible for maintaining law and order, collecting taxes, and managing the hold''s affairs. However, her actual power is largely ceremonial due to the behind-the-scenes control exercised by Maven Black-Briar and the Thieves Guild.', '* Basic combat ability with enchanted weapons befitting a noble * Administrative knowledge of hold management and Nordic law * Diplomatic skills necessary for a Jarl''s duties * Court etiquette and noble customs', 'Laila speaks with the refined diction of Nord nobility, often making proclamations about justice and order that reveal both her good intentions and her naivety. Her speech patterns combine formal court language with occasional shows of maternal concern for her people.', '* Maintain order and prosperity in Riften (though she fails to recognize the true threats) * Support the Stormcloak cause while privately maintaining independence of thought * Restore her son Saerlund to what she considers proper thinking * Protect and serve the people of The Rift to the best of her ability');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lami', 'Lami is a dedicated Nord alchemist and shopkeeper who runs the Thaumaturgist''s Hut in Morthal, serving as both a merchant and alchemy trainer to the local community. She is known for her experimental nature and genuine desire to help others, while maintaining a careful balance between her professional duties and supporting her husband Jorgen.', 'nord, alchemist, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally trained in alchemy by a temple healer who was passing through Morthal on pilgrimage, Lami developed her skills through years of self-taught experimentation and practical application. She established the Thaumaturgist''s Hut to serve Morthal''s alchemical needs, eventually becoming well-known enough to offer training to others interested in the craft.', 'Lami is a warm and welcoming individual who genuinely enjoys helping others with their alchemical needs. She has an experimental and curious nature, often using her spare time to try new alchemical combinations, even though she admits they don''t always work out. Despite living in the relatively isolated town of Morthal, she maintains an optimistic attitude and strong work ethic.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the weathered hands of someone who spends much time working with herbs and alchemical ingredients. She has the sturdy build typical of Nord women, though perhaps slightly softer from spending most of her time indoors at her shop.', '* Jorgen - Her loving husband who shares her dedication to Morthal * Idgrod the Younger - Shows particular concern for her wellbeing and offers to help with her headaches * Morthal Residents - Generally friendly relationships with townspeople who rely on her services * Temple Healer - Former mentor who taught her the basics of alchemy (deceased or departed)', 'Lami owns and operates the Thaumaturgist''s Hut, serving as Morthal''s primary alchemist and supplier of potions and ingredients. She supplements her income by offering training in alchemy to those willing to learn, though she admits to sometimes depleting her own stock through experimentation.', '* Proficient alchemist capable of creating various potions and teaching others * Knowledgeable about local flora and ingredient properties * Basic mercantile skills for running her shop * Self-taught experimental techniques in alchemy', 'Lami speaks in a warm, motherly manner with a typical Nord accent, often using humble and honest language that reflects her experimental nature. She tends to be direct about her successes and failures in alchemy, showing an endearing transparency about her work.', '* Maintain a successful alchemy shop to serve Morthal''s needs * Continue developing her alchemical knowledge through experimentation * Support her husband Jorgen and contribute to Morthal''s wellbeing * Perfect her experimental techniques to create more effective potions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('larina', 'Larina is a talented but naive student at the Bards College whose desperate need for coin led her to make a fatal deal with necromancers. Her story serves as a tragic reminder of how ambition and poor judgment can lead to dire consequences in Skyrim''s harsh world.', 'imperial, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born to a middle-class Imperial family, Larina showed early musical promise and pursued her dreams at the prestigious Bards College in Solitude. Struggling with tuition costs and desperate to maintain her studies, she made the grave mistake of stealing and selling Pantea''s Flute to necromancers, who later captured her for their dark rituals.', 'Initially ambitious and determined, though somewhat reckless in her pursuit of success. Her final moments reveal a terrified young woman who deeply regrets her choices and desperately clings to hope for rescue, showing her true vulnerability beneath her earlier scheming nature.', 'A young Imperial woman in her early twenties with the typical olive-toned skin of her race. Her time in captivity has left her appearing gaunt and disheveled, though traces of her former beauty remain visible despite her dire circumstances.', '* Pantea Ateia - Her instructor at the Bards College, whose trust she betrayed * Necromancers of Hob''s Fall Cave - Her captors and eventual murderers * Bards College Students - Former peers and colleagues * Family - Presumably has relatives in Cyrodiil, though specific details are unknown', 'Student at the Bards College in Solitude, focusing on musical performance and bardic traditions. Her studies were cut short by her imprisonment and eventual death at the hands of necromancers.', '* Trained musician with particular talent for wind instruments * Basic knowledge of bardic lore and performance traditions * Some proficiency in speech and persuasion * Limited understanding of magical theory from her college studies', 'In her final moments, speaks with desperate urgency and growing panic, her educated accent breaking down under extreme stress. Her pleas for help reveal both her terror and her awareness of her impending doom.', '* Complete her education at the Bards College * Escape from her captors in Hob''s Fall Cave * Survive and potentially make amends for her theft * Return to her studies and prove herself worthy of being a bard');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lash_gra-dushnikh', 'Lash gra-Dushnikh is a resilient Orsimer miner who left her stronghold home of Dushnikh Yal to forge her own path in Karthwasten. As both a skilled miner and hunter, she maintains a delicate balance between independence and community involvement while wrestling with her complicated past and Orcish heritage.', 'orc, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in the Orc stronghold of Dushnikh Yal, Lash grew up learning smithing from her mother Gharol but chose to leave due to growing tensions and disagreements about her future role in the stronghold. She eventually found work in Karthwasten''s silver mines, where she built a new life while maintaining loose ties to her Orcish heritage.', 'Lash is fiercely independent and values self-reliance, often keeping others at arm''s length to protect herself from emotional vulnerability. Though generally reserved, she shows loyalty to those who earn her trust and maintains a strong sense of personal honor typical of Orsimer culture. Her gruff exterior masks a complex individual who struggles with balancing her traditional Orcish values against her desire for personal freedom.', 'Lash possesses the characteristic robust build and strong features of an Orsimer female, with prominent lower tusks and thick, dark hair typically worn in practical braids. Her body bears the muscular development common to miners and hunters, with numerous small scars from her work and various confrontations.', '* Gharol - Estranged mother and skilled smith at Dushnikh Yal, relationship marked by tension and unresolved conflicts * Ragnar - Fellow miner whom she respects for his strength and work ethic * Belchimac - Antagonistic coworker whose prejudiced views create workplace tension * Ainethach - Employer and mine owner who treats her fairly despite others'' prejudices', 'Lash works as a silver miner in Karthwasten''s mines, supplementing her income by hunting game in the surrounding wilderness. Her dual role as miner and hunter makes her a valuable member of the community despite some social tensions.', '* Experienced miner with deep knowledge of ore extraction and mining safety * Skilled hunter proficient with bow and tracking techniques * Basic smithing knowledge learned from her mother * Proficient in hand-to-hand combat typical of Orsimer upbringing * Wilderness survival expert', 'Lash speaks in direct, economical sentences with the slight gruffness typical of Orsimer, often dropping pleasantries in favor of getting straight to the point. Her vocabulary reflects her practical nature and stronghold upbringing, though she''s capable of more sophisticated discourse when necessary.', '* Prove herself as a successful independent Orc outside the stronghold system * Eventually reconcile with her mother while maintaining her independence * Earn enough money to potentially start her own mining operation * Gain full acceptance in Karthwasten while preserving her Orcish identity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_adventus_caesennius', 'Legate Adventus Caesennius is a high-ranking Imperial Legion officer stationed at Castle Dour in Solitude who serves as one of General Tullius''s most trusted commanders. A dedicated military leader and staunch supporter of Imperial law, he plays a crucial role in coordinating Legion operations against the Stormcloak rebellion while also recruiting promising candidates to bolster the Empire''s forces in Skyrim.', 'imperial, warrior, haafingar, legion', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Caesennius worked his way up through the Imperial Legion ranks through dedication and tactical prowess. His exemplary service during previous conflicts earned him the position of Legate, and he was specifically chosen to help manage the Empire''s military response to the Stormcloak rebellion in Skyrim.', 'Caesennius is a stern, disciplined military commander who values order, loyalty, and adherence to Imperial law above all else. He displays unwavering confidence in the Empire''s cause and possesses strong persuasive abilities that make him effective at both commanding troops and recruiting new soldiers. Though rigid in his beliefs, he maintains a professional demeanor and shows respect to those who prove themselves worthy.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with a weathered face bearing the scars of numerous battles. His rigid posture and disciplined bearing reflect his military background, while his muscular build speaks to years of combat training and active service.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior officer and commander of Imperial forces in Skyrim * Captain Aldis - Fellow Imperial officer who handles recruit training * Legate Rikke - Colleague and fellow Legate in the Imperial command structure * Stormcloak Leaders - Considered dangerous rebels who must be brought to justice * Local Solitude Guards - Commands their respect through his position and dedication', 'As a Legate in the Imperial Legion, Caesennius serves as a senior military commander responsible for coordinating troops and maintaining Imperial control in Skyrim. He oversees various military operations from his post at Castle Dour while also evaluating and recruiting potential soldiers for the Legion.', '* Expert swordsman trained in Imperial military combat techniques * Skilled tactician with extensive knowledge of military strategy * Natural leader with strong command presence * Proficient archer with Imperial military training * Experienced in logistics and troop coordination', 'Speaks with the formal, authoritative tone of a military commander, using precise language and occasional Imperial military terminology. His speech patterns reflect his education and military background, maintaining professional decorum even in casual conversation.', '* Successfully defeat the Stormcloak rebellion and restore full Imperial control to Skyrim * Maintain order and enforce Imperial law throughout the province * Strengthen the Imperial Legion''s presence in Skyrim through recruitment and training * Prove the superiority of Imperial military discipline and tactics over the rebel forces');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_constantius_tituleius', 'Legate Constantius Tituleius is a dedicated Imperial officer commanding the Legion''s forces in The Pale, representing Imperial authority and military presence in northern Skyrim. A career soldier who embodies the disciplined and orderly nature of the Imperial Legion, he maintains a watchful eye over one of Skyrim''s most contested regions during the Civil War.', 'imperial, warrior, pale, legion', '', '', 'sk_tulius', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Constantius rose through the Legion''s ranks through dedicated service and unwavering loyalty to the Empire. His appointment as Legate in Skyrim came during the rising tensions with the Stormcloaks, where his experience in maintaining order in frontier regions made him an ideal choice for commanding forces in The Pale. His years of service have given him firsthand experience of the Empire''s declining influence, though this has only strengthened his resolve to restore Imperial authority.', 'Constantius is a stern, by-the-book military officer who places tremendous value on discipline and order. He views the world through a pragmatic lens, seeing the Legion''s presence as necessary for maintaining stability rather than as an occupation force. Though he can be rigid in his views, he shows a practical understanding of local recruitment needs and the challenges facing the Empire.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered features and strong bearing of a career soldier. His posture is impeccably straight, reflecting years of military discipline, and his face bears the subtle scars and lines earned through years of service. He maintains the traditional short-cropped hair typical of Imperial officers.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior officer whom he respects and loyally serves * Legate Rikke - Fellow Legate and colleague in the Imperial command structure * Skald the Elder - Antagonistic relationship with the Stormcloak-aligned Jarl of Dawnstar * Local Imperial Soldiers - Commanding officer who maintains professional but firm leadership * Stormcloak Forces - Views them as misguided rebels threatening Imperial order', 'As Legate of the Imperial Legion in The Pale, Constantius commands the Imperial military presence in the region and oversees operations against Stormcloak forces. He manages local recruitment efforts, maintains military discipline, and serves as the Empire''s primary military authority in the region, eventually taking residence in the White Hall if Dawnstar falls under Imperial control.', '* Experienced military commander with tactical expertise in northern warfare * Skilled swordsman trained in Imperial combat techniques * Proficient archer with battlefield experience * Advanced knowledge of military logistics and troop management * Diplomatic skills necessary for managing local relations and recruitment', 'He speaks with the formal, measured tone of an Imperial officer, using military terminology and maintaining professional distance. His speech patterns reflect his education and military background, often emphasizing duty, order, and Imperial authority.', '* Secure The Pale for the Empire and eliminate Stormcloak influence in the region * Maintain Imperial order and stability in northern Skyrim * Strengthen the Legion''s presence through successful local recruitment * Restore full Imperial authority throughout Skyrim * Prove the continued necessity and effectiveness of Imperial governance');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_emmanuel_admand', 'Legate Emmanuel Admand is a disciplined and steadfast Imperial Legion commander who oversees military operations in the Reach during Skyrim''s civil war. A career soldier who rose through Legion ranks, he represents the Empire''s authority and order in one of Skyrim''s most contested regions, maintaining an iron grip on discipline while managing both military strategy and civilian affairs.', 'breton, warrior, reach, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born to a noble Breton family in High Rock, Emmanuel Admand enlisted in the Imperial Legion at a young age, driven by his family''s long tradition of military service. He distinguished himself during the Great War against the Aldmeri Dominion, though the Empire''s eventual capitulation and the White-Gold Concordat left him with a burning determination to prevent further Imperial fragmentation. His exemplary service record and tactical acumen earned him his position as Legate in the Reach, where he has served with unwavering dedication since before the civil war began.', 'Stern, pragmatic, and unyieldingly loyal to the Empire, Admand embodies the disciplined professionalism of the Imperial Legion. He shows little patience for dissent or questioning of Imperial authority, viewing such behavior as a direct threat to stability and order. Though rigid in his beliefs, he maintains a strong sense of duty toward protecting civilian life and maintaining peace in the Reach.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with a soldier''s sturdy build and excellent posture. His face bears the weathered features of a career military man, with sharp eyes and a prominent scar across his left cheek from past battles. His dark hair is kept strictly regulation length, graying at the temples.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior officer whom he respects and loyally serves * Jarl Igmund - Political ally in maintaining Imperial control of Markarth * Local Imperial Soldiers - Commanding officer who demands absolute discipline and loyalty * Forsworn - Views them as dangerous insurgents threatening stability in the Reach * Stormcloaks - Considers them misguided rebels who must be defeated to restore peace', 'As Legate of the Imperial Legion in the Reach, Admand commands all Legion forces in the region and coordinates military operations against both Stormcloak and Forsworn threats. He manages troop deployments, maintains military discipline, and works with local authorities to ensure Imperial control remains strong in this strategically vital hold.', '* Veteran military commander with extensive tactical and strategic expertise * Skilled swordsman trained in Imperial Legion combat techniques * Proficient archer with experience in siege warfare * Expert in military logistics and troop management * Diplomatic skills necessary for managing civilian-military relations', 'Speaks with the clear, authoritative tone of a military commander, using formal language and precise terminology. His speech reflects his military background, often employing tactical terms and maintaining an air of professional detachment.', '* Maintain Imperial control over the Reach and crush the Stormcloak rebellion * Restore complete order and stability to the region under Imperial rule * Strengthen the Empire''s position in Skyrim through military success * Advance within the Imperial Legion''s command structure through loyal service');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_fasendil', 'Legate Fasendil is a unique High Elf Imperial Legion officer who defies typical Altmer stereotypes, serving as the commander of operations in the Rift while secretly monitoring Thalmor activities. His firsthand experience with Thalmor atrocities during the Night of Green Fire has shaped him into a dedicated Imperial loyalist who understands the crucial role the Empire plays in protecting its citizens from Dominion aggression.', 'highelf, warrior, rift, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born to traveling merchant parents who settled in Cyrodiil, Fasendil inherited their wanderlust and joined the Legion to see the world. His defining moment came in 4E 42 while stationed in Hammerfell, where he witnessed the Thalmor''s brutal massacre of Altmer refugees in Sentinel during the Night of Green Fire. This experience fundamentally shaped his views on the Thalmor and led him to request a posting in Skyrim to monitor their activities.', 'Fasendil is principled, dutiful, and deeply committed to the Imperial cause, viewing the Empire as a necessary shield against Thalmor dominance. Despite his military authority, he maintains a philosophical outlook, understanding that bringing order and civilization requires both strength and wisdom. He harbors a deep distrust of the Thalmor based on personal experience, yet remains professional and measured in his approach to duty.', 'As a High Elf, Fasendil possesses the characteristic tall, slender build and golden skin tone of his race, though years of military service have hardened his frame. His face bears the weathered look of a seasoned soldier, with sharp features typical of Altmer ancestry but tempered by exposure to the elements and battlefield experiences.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior officer in the Imperial Legion * Imperial Soldiers - Commanding officer to troops stationed in the Rift * Thalmor - Adversarial relationship based on witnessed atrocities * Altmer Refugees - Sympathetic connection due to shared heritage and witnessed persecution * Laila Law-Giver - Professional relationship as opposing authority in Riften (pre-Imperial control) * Maven Black-Briar - Strategic alliance if Legion takes control of Riften', 'Legate Fasendil serves as the Imperial Legion''s commanding officer in the Rift, responsible for military operations and maintaining Imperial control in the region. His position includes both tactical command of troops and strategic oversight of the hold''s security, while secretly monitoring Thalmor activities in the area.', '* Veteran military commander with extensive battlefield experience * Skilled swordsman trained in Imperial Legion combat techniques * Proficient archer capable of both battlefield and precision shooting * Expert military strategist and tactical commander * Diplomatic skills necessary for managing regional political relations * Intelligence gathering and analysis, particularly regarding Thalmor activities', 'Fasendil speaks with the formal authority of a military commander, employing precise and measured language that reflects both his education and Legion training. His tone carries the weight of command while maintaining diplomatic courtesy, occasionally revealing deeper philosophical insights about duty and civilization.', '* Maintain Imperial control and stability in the Rift * Monitor and counter Thalmor influence in Skyrim * Protect citizens under Imperial rule from both rebel forces and Thalmor machinations * Preserve evidence of Thalmor atrocities to justify continued resistance against their influence * Support the Empire''s broader strategy to eventually challenge Thalmor dominance');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_hrollod', 'Legate Hrollod is a seasoned Nord commander who leads the Imperial forces at the Eastmarch Imperial Camp, demonstrating unwavering loyalty to the Empire despite his Nordic heritage. He represents the complex political dynamics of Skyrim''s civil war, being a Nord who chose Imperial allegiance over traditional Nordic independence.', 'nord, warrior, eastmarch, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Hrollod chose to join the Imperial Legion at a young age, likely due to his belief in the stability and order that the Empire provides. His dedication and tactical abilities earned him the rank of Legate, though his appointment to Eastmarch suggests he has proven himself particularly capable of handling sensitive political situations, given the region''s strong Stormcloak sympathies.', 'Hrollod is pragmatic and duty-focused, viewing the Stormcloak rebellion as a disruption to proper order rather than a legitimate political movement. He demonstrates strong leadership qualities and unwavering loyalty to the Empire, while maintaining a professional demeanor even when dealing with potential recruits or uncertain allies.', 'Hrollod is a sturdy Nord male with the characteristic robust build of his race, bearing the weathered features of a career soldier. His face likely shows the scars and wear of numerous battles, while his posture reflects his military discipline and command presence.', '* General Tullius - Superior officer and commander of Imperial forces in Skyrim * Legate Rikke - Fellow Legate and Nord, sharing similar loyalties to the Empire * Brunwulf Free-Winter - Future political ally if the Imperial Legion prevails * Ulfric Stormcloak - Primary antagonist and target of military operations', 'As Legate of the Eastmarch Imperial Camp, Hrollod commands all Imperial military operations in one of the most strategically important holds in Skyrim. His responsibilities include coordinating attacks against Stormcloak positions, maintaining troop readiness, and managing military resources in the region.', '* Experienced military commander with strategic and tactical expertise * Skilled warrior proficient with both one-handed weapons and archery * Capable leader with strong organizational and command abilities * Diplomatic skills necessary for managing local Nord populations while representing Imperial interests', 'Hrollod speaks with the direct, no-nonsense tone of a military commander, often using formal language that reflects his Imperial training while retaining subtle traces of a Nordic accent. His speech patterns emphasize order, duty, and Imperial authority.', '* Successfully suppress the Stormcloak rebellion in Eastmarch * Maintain Imperial control and stability in the region * Secure a position of influence in Windhelm''s court after an Imperial victory * Prove that Nords can be loyal Imperial citizens while maintaining their cultural identity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_quentin_cipius', 'Legate Quentin Cipius is a high-ranking Imperial Legion officer known for his tactical expertise and unwavering dedication to maintaining Imperial control in Skyrim. As the commander responsible for Whiterun''s defense during the civil war, he exemplifies the disciplined and methodical approach of Imperial military leadership.', 'imperial, warrior, whiterun, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Cipius rose through the ranks of the Imperial Legion through dedication and tactical acumen. His successful military career led to his appointment as a Legate in Skyrim, where he was specifically tasked with coordinating Imperial forces in the Whiterun region during the civil war. His extensive experience in military logistics and siege warfare made him an invaluable asset in defending strategic holdings against the Stormcloak rebellion.', 'Cipius is a stern, protocol-driven military commander who values efficiency and discipline above all else. He maintains a professional demeanor at all times, showing little patience for incompetence or deviation from proper military procedure. Despite his rigid exterior, he demonstrates genuine concern for his troops'' wellbeing and takes practical measures to ensure their survival, as shown by his proactive approach to organizing water brigades during the siege of Whiterun.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered appearance of a career soldier, bearing the physical fitness and straight-backed posture typical of long-serving military officers. His face shows the lines and scars of numerous campaigns, while his bearing reflects years of command experience.', '* Jarl Balgruuf the Greater - Professional military alliance, though occasionally tense due to cultural differences * General Tullius - Direct superior officer in the Imperial Legion chain of command * Irileth - Collaborative relationship as fellow military advisors to Jarl Balgruuf * Imperial Soldiers - Commanding officer who demands respect and maintains strict discipline * Stormcloak Rebels - Sworn enemies whom he views as traitors to the Empire', 'As a Legate in the Imperial Legion, Cipius serves as a senior military commander responsible for coordinating Imperial forces and strategy in the Whiterun region. He functions as both a tactical advisor to local authorities and a field commander, managing troop deployments and defensive preparations against Stormcloak aggression.', '* Expert tactician with particular expertise in siege warfare and defensive operations * Accomplished swordsman trained in Imperial military combat techniques * Proficient archer capable of both battlefield and defensive wall combat * Strong command and leadership abilities honed through years of military service * Advanced knowledge of military logistics and strategic planning', 'Speaks in a formal, authoritative tone befitting his military rank, using precise language and maintaining professional decorum at all times. His speech patterns reflect Imperial military training, with clear, direct commands and an emphasis on proper titles and protocol.', '* Maintain Imperial control over Whiterun and surrounding territories * Crush the Stormcloak rebellion and restore full Imperial authority in Skyrim * Ensure the survival and combat effectiveness of troops under his command * Strengthen Whiterun''s defenses against potential future threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_rikke', 'Legate Rikke is a fierce Nord warrior who serves as General Tullius'' second-in-command in the Imperial Legion, embodying the complex dynamic between Nordic tradition and Imperial loyalty. Despite her heritage, she firmly believes that Skyrim''s best chance for survival lies with the Empire, making her a controversial but respected figure in the Civil War.', 'imperial, warrior, noble, skyrimall, legion', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born to Legion parents in Skyrim, Rikke followed their footsteps and joined the Imperial Legion at a young age. She fought alongside Ulfric Stormcloak and Galmar Stone-Fist during the Great War against the Aldmeri Dominion, forming bonds that would later be tested by civil conflict. Her experiences in the Great War and witnessing the Empire''s struggles against the Dominion shaped her conviction that only a united Empire could stand against future Thalmor aggression.', 'Rikke is pragmatic, disciplined, and deeply loyal to both the Empire and her Nordic heritage, often finding herself torn between these dual identities. She maintains a stoic and professional demeanor, though occasionally reveals moments of regret when confronting former friends turned enemies. While respectful of Nord traditions, she prioritizes practical military necessity over cultural sentimentality.', 'A battle-hardened Nord woman with weathered features that reflect years of military service. She maintains a warrior''s physique and carries herself with a soldier''s disciplined posture. Her face bears the subtle scars of combat experience, while her eyes reflect both determination and world-weariness.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior and trusted commander whom she respects despite cultural differences * Ulfric Stormcloak - Former friend and fellow soldier, now bitter enemy * Galmar Stone-Fist - Once-close companion from the Great War, turned adversary * Imperial Legion - Loyalty inherited from parents and strengthened through service * Nordic People - Complex relationship as both defender and perceived betrayer', 'Legate Rikke serves as Chief Lieutenant of the Imperial Legion in Skyrim, acting as General Tullius'' second-in-command and primary military advisor. She oversees troop movements, battle strategy, and maintains the crucial link between Imperial command and Nordic cultural understanding.', '* Master-level heavy armor and one-handed combat specialist * Expert military tactician and strategist * Proficient shield bearer with defensive combat expertise * Natural leader with strong command abilities * Intimate knowledge of Nordic customs and warfare traditions', 'Speaks with authoritative military precision, tempering Imperial formality with Nordic directness. Her tone carries the weight of command while occasionally revealing traces of her Nordic accent, especially when emotional.', '* Reunify Skyrim under Imperial control to strengthen defenses against the Thalmor * End the Civil War with minimal bloodshed and destruction * Preserve Nordic culture while maintaining Imperial authority * Prove that being a true Nord and a loyal Imperial are not mutually exclusive');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_sevan_telendas', 'Legate Sevan Telendas is a seasoned Dark Elf military commander who leads the Imperial Legion''s operations in Winterhold with tactical precision and unwavering loyalty to the Empire. As field commander of the Winterhold Imperial Camp, he represents the Empire''s authority in one of Skyrim''s most challenging regions while managing local recruitment efforts and strategic operations against the Stormcloak rebellion.', 'darkelf, warrior, winterhold, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Sevan chose to serve the Empire rather than remain in his troubled homeland after the Red Year. He rose through the Legion''s ranks through demonstrated leadership and tactical acumen, eventually earning his position as Legate despite the prejudices often faced by Dark Elves in Imperial service. His extensive military experience and proven loyalty led to his current posting in Winterhold, where he works to maintain Imperial control in one of Skyrim''s most hostile environments.', 'Sevan is a pragmatic and disciplined officer who maintains professional detachment while executing his duties. He shows particular disdain for the Stormcloak rebellion, viewing it as a disruption of order that must be quelled for the greater good of the Empire. Though stern in his command, he demonstrates a practical understanding of the need to recruit locally and adapt to Skyrim''s challenging political climate.', 'A weathered Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, hardened by years of military service. His bearing is straight and proud, reflecting his military discipline, with a muscular build maintained through regular combat training. His face bears the stern expression typical of career military officers, with subtle scarring from past battles.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior officer who oversees all Legion operations in Skyrim * Legate Rikke - Fellow Legate and colleague in the Imperial command structure * Winterhold Guards - Professional command relationship with local Imperial-aligned forces * Korir - Adversarial relationship with the Stormcloak-aligned Jarl of Winterhold', 'As Legate and field commander of the Winterhold Imperial Camp, Sevan oversees all Legion military operations in the Winterhold region. His responsibilities include maintaining troop readiness, coordinating strategic movements against Stormcloak forces, and managing local recruitment efforts. Should Winterhold fall to Imperial control, he assumes a leadership position in the city itself, representing Imperial authority.', '* Experienced military commander with extensive tactical and strategic knowledge * Skilled swordsman proficient with both one-handed weapons and archery * Advanced knowledge of Imperial military protocols and procedures * Capable leader with strong organizational and command abilities * Survival expert adapted to Winterhold''s harsh climate', 'Speaks with the formal, measured tone of an Imperial officer, frequently using military terminology and maintaining professional distance. His vocabulary reflects his education and command position, while his slight Dunmer accent adds gravity to his words.', '* Secure and maintain Imperial control over Winterhold and its surrounding regions * Crush the Stormcloak rebellion and restore full Imperial authority in Skyrim * Prove that non-Nords can serve the Empire with distinction and earn respect through merit * Establish a stable Imperial presence in Winterhold that can withstand both political and natural challenges');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_skulnar', 'Legate Skulnar is a seasoned Nord officer in the Imperial Legion who serves as the military governor of Falkreath Hold when under Imperial control. A staunch defender of Imperial law and order, he represents the Empire''s authority in southern Skyrim while coordinating efforts to suppress the Stormcloak rebellion in the region.', 'nord, warrior, falkreath, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Skulnar chose to serve the Empire from a young age, rising through the Legion''s ranks through dedication and loyalty. His extensive military service and understanding of both Imperial and Nordic cultures made him an ideal choice for maintaining order in Falkreath Hold, a strategic location bordering Cyrodiil. Having witnessed the deterioration of peace in his homeland, he became increasingly convinced that only Imperial rule could restore stability to Skyrim.', 'Skulnar is a pragmatic and duty-bound officer who values order and stability above all else. He shows little patience for rebellion or chaos, viewing the Stormcloak uprising as a dangerous disruption to peace rather than a legitimate cause. Though proud of his Nord heritage, he believes that prosperity comes through unity with the Empire rather than independence.', 'A weathered Nord warrior in his late forties with the sturdy build typical of his race. His face bears the scars of numerous battles, and his stern countenance reflects years of military discipline. His posture remains impeccably straight, betraying his years of Imperial military training.', '* General Tullius - Superior officer and commander of Imperial forces in Skyrim * Legate Rikke - Fellow Nord Legate, shares similar views on Skyrim''s place in the Empire * Siddgeir - Jarl of Falkreath when under Imperial control, maintains professional relationship * Local Imperial Soldiers - Commands their respect through fair leadership and experience * Stormcloak Forces - Views them as misguided rebels threatening Skyrim''s stability', 'As Legate of the Imperial Legion, Skulnar serves as the military governor of Falkreath Hold when under Imperial control. His duties include maintaining order, coordinating troop movements, and ensuring the security of the strategic southern border with Cyrodiil. When Stormcloaks control Falkreath, he leads resistance efforts from the Imperial camp.', '* Veteran warrior skilled in both one-handed swordsmanship and archery * Experienced military commander with strategic planning abilities * Proficient in heavy armor combat techniques * Skilled in military logistics and troop coordination * Knowledge of Imperial military protocols and procedures', 'Speaks with the formal, authoritative tone of an Imperial officer while retaining hints of his Nordic accent. His speech is direct and professional, often focusing on military matters and the importance of maintaining order.', '* Restore and maintain Imperial control over Falkreath Hold * End the Stormcloak rebellion to bring stability back to Skyrim * Protect the strategic southern border between Skyrim and Cyrodiil * Strengthen the Imperial Legion''s presence in southern Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('legate_taurinus_duilis', 'Legate Taurinus Duilis is a seasoned Imperial Legion officer stationed in Morthal, where he serves as the military commander for Hjaalmarch Hold. A dedicated career soldier and tactical strategist, he represents the Empire''s authority in this remote region of Skyrim while coordinating military operations against the Stormcloak rebellion.', 'imperial, warrior, hjaalmarch, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Taurinus worked his way up through the Imperial Legion ranks through dedication and tactical acumen. He earned his position as Legate through years of faithful service and demonstrated leadership during various military campaigns, eventually being assigned to the strategically important but challenging post in Morthal to maintain Imperial control in the region.', 'Taurinus is a pragmatic and dutiful officer who takes his responsibilities seriously, demonstrating unwavering loyalty to the Empire and its ideals. He approaches his duties with a methodical mindset, showing particular skill in strategic planning and maintaining order through disciplined military presence. Though stern and formal in his dealings, he maintains a professional respect for both his soldiers and cooperative civilians.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered features and strong bearing of a career soldier. His face bears the subtle scars of combat experience, while his rigid posture and calculated movements reflect his military discipline. He maintains the traditional short-cropped hair of Imperial military tradition.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior officer and commander of Imperial forces in Skyrim * Legate Rikke - Fellow Legate and colleague in the Imperial command structure * Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - Local authority figure with whom he must coordinate * Local Imperial Soldiers - Troops under his direct command * Stormcloak Forces - Primary adversaries in the civil war', 'As Legate of the Imperial Legion in Morthal, Taurinus oversees all military operations and strategic planning in Hjaalmarch Hold. His responsibilities include maintaining Imperial control, coordinating troop movements, and serving as the primary military authority in the region.', '* Expert tactician and military strategist * Proficient with both sword and bow in combat * Skilled commander with experience leading troops * Advanced knowledge of Imperial military protocols and procedures * Capable of both close-quarters combat and ranged warfare', 'Speaks with the formal, disciplined tone of an Imperial officer, using proper military terminology and maintaining professional decorum. His speech patterns reflect his education and military background, often employing strategic and diplomatic language when discussing the civil war.', '* Maintain Imperial control over Hjaalmarch Hold and suppress Stormcloak influence * Ensure the successful implementation of Imperial military strategy in northern Skyrim * Restore and maintain order in his assigned region * Advance the Imperial Legion''s interests while minimizing civilian casualties');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('leifnarr', 'Leifnarr was a Nord farmer who met a tragic end in Broken Helm Hollow, leaving behind his wife Grosta at Heartwood Mill. A hardworking and respected member of his rural community, his mysterious death serves as a reminder of Skyrim''s dangerous wilderness.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in the rural areas of The Rift, Leifnarr spent his life working the land and building a modest farming operation near Heartwood Mill. He married Grosta and together they established themselves as respected members of their small farming community, known for their hard work and reliability.', 'Leifnarr was characterized by his strong work ethic and friendly demeanor, often willing to help neighbors with their harvests or share farming knowledge. He was known for his practical approach to life and strong sense of Nordic traditions, though his trusting nature may have ultimately contributed to his demise.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the weathered complexion typical of those who work outdoors. His hands were calloused from years of farming, and his body was well-muscled from daily physical labor.', '* Grosta - His devoted wife who operates Heartwood Mill * Local Farmers - Maintained friendly relationships with neighboring homesteaders * Trading Caravans - Regular business contacts for selling crops * Riften Merchants - Occasional business dealings in the city', 'Leifnarr worked as a farmer, cultivating crops and maintaining his homestead near Heartwood Mill. He supplemented his income by trading with passing caravans and occasionally selling surplus at the Riften market.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of crop cultivation * Capable woodworker and basic carpenter * Basic combat abilities typical of Nordic farmers * Skilled in animal husbandry and livestock management', 'Spoke with a thick Nordic accent and used simple, direct language common among rural farmers. His vocabulary focused on practical matters and traditional Nordic sayings.', '* Expand his farming operation to ensure a comfortable life for himself and Grosta * Maintain a respected position within the local farming community * Save enough gold to eventually purchase additional land near Heartwood Mill');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('leifur', 'Leifur is a dedicated Nord lumberjack at Anga''s Mill who exemplifies the strong work ethic and simple values of his people. He maintains a positive outlook despite the demanding physical labor, often serving as a counterbalance to his more pessimistic co-worker''s attitude while quietly observing the comings and goings at the mill.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in the Eastmarch region of Skyrim, Leifur found his calling in the lumber industry from an early age. He has worked at Anga''s Mill for several years, having proven himself reliable enough to earn Aeri''s trust and a permanent position at the mill. His steady nature and consistent work helped him maintain his position even after the mysterious departure of his former co-worker Ennodius Papius.', 'Leifur possesses a calm, good-natured disposition and finds genuine satisfaction in honest work. He demonstrates emotional intelligence in his interactions, using humor to deflect tension and maintain workplace harmony, particularly when dealing with Kodrir''s complaints. While generally easygoing, he''s not afraid to stand up to negativity with witty responses.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. His hands are calloused from years of handling lumber and tools, and his skin shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Aeri - Employer who trusts him as a reliable worker * Kodrir - Fellow lumberjack and housemate with whom he maintains a tolerant but teasing relationship * Ennodius Papius - Former co-worker whose mysterious departure occasionally concerns him', 'Leifur works as a full-time lumberjack at Anga''s Mill, performing various tasks including chopping trees, carrying logs, and operating the sawmill. His position requires him to maintain a strict daily schedule, working from early morning until evening with regular shifts between different lumber-related tasks.', '* Experienced woodcutter with extensive knowledge of lumber work * Proficient in operating and maintaining sawmill equipment * Physical strength and endurance from years of manual labor * Basic weapon handling for self-defense with an iron dagger', 'Leifur speaks in a straightforward, casual manner typical of working-class Nords, often employing dry wit and gentle sarcasm. His vocabulary is simple but effective, and he shows a particular talent for deflecting tension with humor.', '* Maintain his stable position at Anga''s Mill and continue earning an honest living * Keep workplace harmony despite Kodrir''s negative attitude * Potentially uncover the truth about Ennodius Papius''s disappearance, though not actively pursuing it');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('leigelf', 'Leigelf is a determined and prideful Nord mine owner in Dawnstar who operates the Quicksilver Mine in direct competition with his estranged wife''s Iron-Breaker Mine. His life is defined by his bitter feud with Beitild and his unwavering dedication to proving the superiority of his mining operation, though his personal journal suggests deeper, unresolved feelings for his wife.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Dawnstar, Leigelf worked his way up from a common miner to eventually acquiring ownership of the Quicksilver Mine. He married Beitild during more prosperous times, but their relationship deteriorated into a bitter rivalry after both became mine owners, leading them to live separately despite remaining legally married.', 'Leigelf is stubborn, proud, and deeply competitive, particularly regarding his mining operation. While he maintains a tough exterior and openly expresses disdain for his wife, his private writings suggest a more complex emotional state. He values loyalty in his workers and demonstrates a strong work ethic, often pushing himself to exhaustion.', 'A weathered Nord male with the muscular build typical of someone who has spent decades working in mines. His hands are calloused from years of mining, and his face shows the wear of long hours working outdoors in Dawnstar''s harsh climate.', '* Beitild - Estranged wife and rival mine owner, relationship deteriorated into bitter feud * Lond - Loyal employee who shows genuine concern for his well-being * Skald the Elder - Respects his authority as Jarl but views him as somewhat immature * Mine Workers - Maintains professional relationships though their sleep is affected by shared nightmares', 'Leigelf owns and operates the Quicksilver Mine in Dawnstar, handling both the business operations and participating in the physical mining work. He personally works the smelter alongside his employees and manages ore sales, maintaining a hands-on approach to his business.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of quicksilver ore extraction * Proficient with mining tools and smelting equipment * Basic business management and trading abilities * Physical stamina and strength from years of manual labor', 'Speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with the rough accent typical of Dawnstar Nords. Often makes competitive remarks about his mine''s superiority and dismissive comments about Iron-Breaker Mine.', '* Prove the superiority of Quicksilver Mine over Iron-Breaker Mine * Drive Beitild out of business to force an apology from her * Maintain his position as a respected mine owner in Dawnstar * Find resolution to the nightmares plaguing him and his workers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lemkil', 'Lemkil is a bitter, widowed Nord farmer in Rorikstead whose wife''s death during childbirth has left him a cold and cruel single father to twin daughters. His harsh demeanor and negligent parenting have made him notorious within the small farming community, where he channels his grief and anger into working his fields while showing little care or affection for his children.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally a more optimistic farmer, Lemkil''s life changed dramatically when his beloved wife died giving birth to their twin daughters, Sissel and Britte. The loss transformed him into a bitter man who blames his daughters for their mother''s death, viewing them as a constant reminder of his loss rather than a blessing. He has spent the years since then focusing solely on his farmwork while emotionally abandoning his parental duties.', 'Lemkil is characterized by his overwhelming bitterness, quick temper, and emotional coldness, particularly toward his own children. He harbors deep-seated grief that manifests as cruelty and dismissiveness, rejecting help from concerned neighbors and responding to most social interactions with hostility. His stubborn nature prevents him from accepting his role in his daughters'' unhappiness, instead choosing to blame them for his misfortunes.', 'A weather-beaten Nord of middle age, with callused hands and a perpetual scowl etched into his features from years of fieldwork and bitterness. His sturdy frame shows the physical conditioning of daily farm labor, though stress and hardship have aged him beyond his years.', '* Sissel - Younger twin daughter whom he neglects and verbally abuses * Britte - Elder twin daughter who has adopted his bitter nature * Jouane Manette - Concerned neighbor who attempts to help the family * Rorik - Local landlord who shows concern for his daughters * Mralki - Inn owner who disapproves of his parenting * Erik - Young villager who confronts him about his cruelty', 'Lemkil works as a farmer in Rorikstead, maintaining fields of crops including cabbages, leeks, and potatoes. He spends twelve hours daily tending to his crops, taking pride in his agricultural work while neglecting his domestic responsibilities.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of crop cultivation * Physical endurance developed through years of agricultural labor * Basic trading and bartering abilities for selling crops * Survival skills necessary for living off the land', 'Lemkil speaks in harsh, bitter tones filled with complaints and criticism, particularly about his daughters. His vocabulary is simple and direct, reflecting his rural background and tendency to express negative emotions openly.', '* Maintain his farm''s productivity as his sole source of pride and income * Avoid confronting his grief and responsibility for his daughters'' welfare * Continue his self-imposed isolation from the community''s attempts to help');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('leonara_arius', 'Leonara Arius is a resilient Imperial farmer who found love and a fresh start at Snow-Shod Farm after leaving her life in Cyrodiil behind. Despite her contentment in her new marriage and simple farming life, she carries both emotional scars from her past family conflicts and present anxieties about the civil war threatening her newfound happiness.', 'imperial, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Leonara experienced a significant falling out with her family that prompted her to leave her homeland and seek a new life in Skyrim. By fate or fortune, the first door she knocked on in Skyrim was that of Snow-Shod Farm, where she met Addvild, who would become her husband. Her transition from city life in Cyrodiil to farming in Skyrim marks a dramatic change in her life circumstances.', 'Leonara is warm-hearted and deeply appreciative of the simple pleasures in life, particularly the love she shares with her husband. She shows remarkable resilience in rebuilding her life after family trauma, though she carries an underlying fear of losing her new family. While generally optimistic, she displays practical concern about security matters affecting the farm.', 'As an Imperial woman, Leonara likely has the characteristic olive-toned skin and dark hair common to her race. Her daily work in the fields has likely given her a sturdy, work-hardened physique, though she maintains a feminine appearance. Her hands show the calluses and weathering typical of a farmer''s life.', '* Addvild - Beloved husband and partner in managing Snow-Shod Farm * Snow-Shod Family - Employers and extended support network * Cyrodiil Family - Estranged relations with whom she had a falling out * Local Guards - Professional relationship tinged with concern about their limited numbers', 'Leonara works as a farmer at Snow-Shod Farm, where she tends to the crops daily from early morning until nightfall. Her responsibilities include maintaining the fields, managing crop rotation, and ensuring the farm''s productivity alongside her husband. She takes pride in her agricultural work despite it being a significant departure from her previous city life.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Capable of wielding a dagger for self-defense * Adaptable personality, demonstrated by successful transition from city to farm life * Basic domestic skills including cooking and household management', 'Leonara speaks with genuine warmth and sincerity, often expressing gratitude for her current life and deep affection for her husband. Her manner of speech reflects her Imperial background but has likely adopted some Nordic influences since moving to Skyrim.', '* Maintain and strengthen her marriage with Addvild * Build a successful and secure life at Snow-Shod Farm * Protect her new family from the threats of civil war * Eventually start a family of her own with Addvild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('leontius_salvius', 'Leontius Salvius is a diligent Imperial innkeeper''s assistant at the Old Hroldan Inn, who eventually assumes full management responsibilities upon the death of his employer Eydis. Though lacking the historical storytelling flair of his predecessor, he maintains the inn''s operations with a professional demeanor while balancing his connection to his family''s farming legacy.', 'imperial, innkeeper, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born to farming parents Rogatus and Vigdis at Salvius Farm, Leontius chose to pursue work at the Old Hroldan Inn rather than continue in agriculture. His decision to work under Eydis likely stems from a desire to forge his own path while remaining close enough to maintain family ties. Though trained in farming from youth, he has adapted to innkeeping duties through years of service.', 'Leontius exhibits a pragmatic and dutiful nature, showing strong work ethic in his daily routines. He maintains a professional and courteous demeanor with guests, though lacks the storytelling passion of Eydis, suggesting a more practical approach to innkeeping. His willingness to assume full responsibility after Eydis''s death demonstrates reliability and commitment to his duties.', 'As an Imperial man, Leontius likely possesses the typical features of his race - a medium build with fair to olive skin tone. His years of outdoor work have likely weathered his appearance somewhat, with callused hands and sun-touched skin from daily labor.', '* Eydis - Employer and mentor in the innkeeping trade * Skuli - Eydis''s son and technical owner of the inn after her death * Rogatus - Father who maintains correspondence through letters * Vigdis - Mother who runs Salvius Farm with his father', 'Leontius serves as a general worker at Old Hroldan Inn, performing outdoor maintenance and various innkeeping duties. Upon Eydis''s death, he assumes the role of primary innkeeper, managing room rentals and daily operations while working under Skuli''s ownership.', '* Proficient in general inn maintenance and outdoor labor * Capable of basic business management and guest relations * Experienced in farming techniques from his upbringing * Basic combat ability with an iron dagger for self-defense', 'Leontius speaks in a direct, practical manner, focusing on necessary information rather than embellishment. His tone is polite and professional, befitting his service-oriented position.', '* Maintain the successful operation of Old Hroldan Inn while honoring Eydis''s memory * Balance his innkeeping duties with maintaining family connections * Establish himself as a respected innkeeper in his own right');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lieutenant_salvarus', 'Lieutenant Salvarus is a high-ranking Penitus Oculatus officer serving as second-in-command aboard Emperor Titus Mede II''s personal vessel, The Katariah. A model of Imperial discipline and loyalty, he represents the elite standard of the Emperor''s security force, maintaining strict vigilance over the sovereign''s safety during maritime voyages.', 'imperial, noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born and raised in the Imperial City, Salvarus worked his way up through the Imperial Legion ranks before being selected for the prestigious Penitus Oculatus. His exceptional service record and unwavering loyalty to the Empire earned him his current position as the Emperor''s maritime security chief, where he oversees the safety protocols aboard The Katariah.', 'Salvarus embodies the professional stoicism and rigid discipline expected of high-ranking Imperial officers. He maintains an air of formal authority at all times, showing unwavering dedication to his duties and expecting nothing less than excellence from those under his command. Though stern, he treats his subordinates with respect and fairness, earning their loyalty through exemplary leadership.', 'A well-built Imperial man in his late thirties or early forties, with the hardened physique of a career soldier. His face bears the weathered features common to those who spend considerable time at sea, with sharp eyes constantly scanning for potential threats and a strong, commanding presence in his bearing.', '* Emperor Titus Mede II - Direct superior and primary protection responsibility * Commander Maro - Superior officer in the Penitus Oculatus * Ship''s Captain - Works closely to coordinate security measures * Penitus Oculatus Guards - Direct subordinates under his command', 'As Lieutenant of the Penitus Oculatus and second-in-command of The Katariah''s security detail, Salvarus oversees all aspects of the Emperor''s maritime protection. He coordinates guard rotations, maintains security protocols, and personally inspects all security measures aboard the vessel.', '* Expert swordsman trained in Imperial Legion combat techniques * Advanced knowledge of maritime security protocols and ship defense * Leadership and tactical command expertise * Highly trained in VIP protection and threat assessment * Proficient in Imperial naval operations and ship navigation', 'Speaks with the formal, authoritative tone of a high-ranking Imperial officer, using proper military terminology and maintaining professional decorum at all times. His speech is clear and direct, reflecting his military background and command position.', '* Ensure the absolute safety and security of Emperor Titus Mede II during maritime travel * Maintain the highest standards of security aboard The Katariah * Uphold the honor and reputation of the Penitus Oculatus * Advance within the ranks of the Emperor''s security force');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lillith_maiden-loom', 'Lillith Maiden-Loom is a shrewd businesswoman and respected elder of Whiterun who owns and manages the city''s stables through her employee Skulvar Sable-Hilt. Despite her gentle demeanor, she is a savvy entrepreneur who has maintained her business through both peaceful and turbulent times, serving as a cornerstone of Whiterun''s merchant community.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born into a merchant family in Whiterun, Lillith inherited the stables from her late husband, a skilled horse trainer who established the business decades ago. She has weathered numerous challenges including bandit raids, civil unrest, and economic hardships, adapting her business practices while maintaining the stables'' reputation for quality horses. Her years of experience have made her an influential figure in Whiterun''s commercial sphere.', 'Lillith presents a warm, motherly demeanor that masks her sharp business acumen and careful judgment of character. She maintains a delicate balance between the Battle-Born and Gray-Mane factions, refusing to take sides in their feud while maintaining profitable relationships with both. Though generally friendly, she is cautious with strangers and protective of her business interests.', 'A Nord woman in her late sixties with silver-white hair and weathered features that speak to a lifetime spent partially outdoors. Despite her age, she maintains an straight-backed, dignified bearing and moves with surprising energy. Her face bears the gentle wrinkles of someone who has smiled often throughout their life.', '* Skulvar Sable-Hilt - Trusted employee and stable master who handles daily operations * Fralia Gray-Mane - Close friend and confidante in the marketplace * Battle-Born Family - Business associates who regularly purchase horses * Gray-Mane Family - Long-standing customers and friends * Various Merchants - Part of Whiterun''s trading network', 'Lillith is the owner and proprietor of Whiterun Stables, managing the business aspects while leaving the hands-on horse care to her employee. She oversees all major transactions, maintains business relationships with important clients, and handles the financial aspects of the operation.', '* Expert in business management and horse trading * Knowledgeable about horse breeds, care, and values * Skilled negotiator and saleswoman * Adept at maintaining complex social and business relationships * Basic understanding of animal husbandry and stable management', 'Her speech is warm and maternal, peppered with terms of endearment like ''dear'' and ''love,'' but can shift to a more businesslike tone when necessary. She speaks with the measured pace and subtle authority of someone accustomed to being heard and respected.', '* Maintain the stables'' reputation as the finest horse-trading establishment in Whiterun Hold * Secure the future of her business through the civil war and beyond * Find a suitable successor to eventually take over the stables * Preserve her neutral standing in Whiterun''s political climate');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('linwe', 'Linwe is a cunning High Elf criminal mastermind who leads the Summerset Shadows, a rival organization to the Thieves Guild operating in Windhelm. Unlike typical thieves, he specializes in grave robbery and stealing from the recently deceased, maintaining a sophisticated operation through careful planning and delegation.', 'highelf, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally from the Summerset Isles, Linwe established himself in Skyrim after recognizing an opportunity to create a specialized theft operation focusing on the dead. He likely gained his initial criminal experience in his homeland before moving north, where he recruited like-minded thieves to form the Summerset Shadows and established a profitable partnership with Niranye in Windhelm.', 'Linwe is calculating, methodical, and morally flexible, viewing the dead as ideal targets due to their inability to fight back. He maintains a professional distance from his fence and operates with careful planning rather than impulsive action, suggesting a sophisticated criminal mind that values efficiency over honor.', 'As a High Elf, Linwe possesses the characteristic tall, slender build and sharp, angular features of his race. His skin has the typical golden hue of the Altmer, and he maintains an aristocratic bearing despite his criminal lifestyle.', '* Niranye - Business partner and fence in Windhelm, though they rarely meet in person * Summerset Shadows - Leader and commander of this criminal organization * Thieves Guild - Rival organization that sees his operation as a threat * Various Windhelm citizens - Victims and targets of his grave-robbing operation', 'Linwe serves as the leader and mastermind of the Summerset Shadows, orchestrating their grave-robbing operations from Uttering Hills Cave. He manages the organization''s activities, plans heists, and maintains connections with fences while keeping a low profile.', '* Expert in stealth and infiltration, particularly in accessing secured burial sites * Advanced leadership and organizational abilities * Skilled at planning and executing complex heists * Proficient in light armor combat techniques * Expert at appraising valuable goods and artifacts', 'Linwe speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary typical of Altmer nobility, though his tone often carries underlying hints of condescension and superiority. He maintains a professional demeanor in his communications, as evidenced by his written correspondence.', '* Expand the influence and territory of the Summerset Shadows throughout Skyrim * Maintain dominance over the grave-robbing trade in Windhelm * Accumulate wealth while avoiding direct confrontation with the Thieves Guild * Establish a more sophisticated criminal network that rivals the Thieves Guild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lisbet', 'Lisbet is a widowed Nord merchant who runs the Arnleif and Sons Trading Company in Markarth after inheriting it from her late husband. She is a determined businesswoman struggling to maintain her store''s prosperity amid frequent Forsworn attacks, while hiding a dark secret that threatens to destroy everything she''s built.', 'nord, merchant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally from Markarth, Lisbet married into the merchant family that owned Arnleif and Sons Trading Company. After her husband Gunnar was killed in a Forsworn attack five years ago, she took over management of the store, maintaining its operations despite increasingly difficult circumstances and dwindling trade routes.', 'Lisbet presents herself as a stern, pragmatic businesswoman with a no-nonsense approach to running her store. She can be harsh with her employees but shows appreciation to those who help her business. Behind this facade, she harbors darker impulses and secrets, demonstrating remarkable ability to maintain a respectable public image while concealing her true nature.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the weathered features typical of someone who has spent years managing a business in the harsh climate of the Reach. She maintains a neat, professional appearance befitting a merchant of her standing, with the strong physical constitution characteristic of her Nord heritage.', '* Gunnar (Deceased) - Her late husband who was killed by the Forsworn * Imedhnain - Employee who she frequently scolds for poor performance * Cosnach - Unreliable worker who often drinks instead of working * Ogmund - She admires his singing at the inn * Local Merchants - Professional relationships within Markarth''s trading community', 'Owner and proprietor of Arnleif and Sons Trading Company, one of Markarth''s primary general goods stores. She manages all aspects of the business, from inventory and accounts to employee supervision and customer relations, while dealing with the challenges of maintaining trade routes in the dangerous Reach region.', '* Experienced merchant with strong bargaining and business management abilities * Skilled at maintaining detailed ledgers and tracking inventory * Proficient in basic weapon use for self-defense * Expert at maintaining a respectable public image while concealing secrets', 'She speaks in a direct, businesslike manner, often curt but professional. Her vocabulary reflects her merchant background, frequently discussing trade, coin, and business matters while maintaining formality with customers.', '* Maintain the profitability of Arnleif and Sons Trading Company despite regional instability * Secure trade routes against Forsworn attacks * Preserve her husband''s legacy through the continued success of the store * Keep her darker activities hidden from public knowledge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lisette', 'Lisette is a talented Breton bard and graduate of the Bards College who has chosen the life of a tavern performer at the Winking Skeever in Solitude. Rather than pursuing a more prestigious position, she finds fulfillment in entertaining common folk with her music while documenting notable events in song, as evidenced by her interest in recording Roggvir''s execution for the Edda.', 'breton, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Lisette traveled to Skyrim to study at the prestigious Bards College in Solitude. After graduating, she made the conscious choice to remain in the city but work at the Winking Skeever rather than pursue a more formal position at the College, preferring the authentic connection with common people that tavern performance provides.', 'Lisette is a warm and welcoming individual who takes genuine pleasure in entertaining others and creating a comfortable atmosphere through her music. While serious about her craft and diligent in documenting historical events through song, she maintains a light-hearted demeanor and values the simple pleasures of good company over prestige or wealth. She displays both professional pride in her abilities and humble contentment with her chosen path.', 'As a Breton, Lisette has the characteristic shorter stature and slender build common to her race. Her hands show the slight calluses of a dedicated lute player, and she carries herself with the good posture typical of trained performers.', '* Corpulus Vinius - Employer and owner of the Winking Skeever * Una - Fellow bard and occasional conversation partner * Vivienne Onis - College associate with whom she discusses music and events * Viarmo - Former instructor at the Bards College * Regular patrons of the Winking Skeever - Valued audience members who provide her livelihood', 'Lisette serves as the resident bard at the Winking Skeever, performing music, taking requests, and documenting notable events in song. Her position requires her to entertain guests throughout the day and maintain a welcoming atmosphere in the tavern.', '* Accomplished lute player with formal training from the Bards College * Skilled vocalist capable of performing the traditional songs of Skyrim * Practiced storyteller and keeper of oral histories * Basic self-defense abilities as evidenced by her carried weapons', 'Lisette speaks in a warm, inviting manner with the refined diction of a formally trained bard, though she maintains an approachable tone that puts common folk at ease. Her vocabulary reflects her education while remaining accessible to her tavern audience.', '* Build a comprehensive repertoire of songs documenting important events in Solitude * Maintain her position as a respected tavern performer while staying connected to the Bards College community * Perfect her craft while continuing to provide comfort and entertainment to weary travelers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lleril_morvayn', 'Lleril Morvayn is the dignified and compassionate Dunmer ruler of Raven Rock, serving as House Redoran''s Councilor on Solstheim. A skilled diplomat and traditionalist, he leads his people through challenging times while maintaining the values and customs of House Redoran, despite the settlement''s declining fortunes.', 'darkelf, noble, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_lleril', '', 'Born into House Redoran nobility, Lleril inherited his position from his mother Brara in 4E 65, continuing a legacy of leadership in Raven Rock. He has witnessed the settlement''s gradual decline following the Red Year and the closure of the ebony mines, yet remains steadfastly committed to restoring Raven Rock to its former glory. His leadership has been marked by both successes and challenges, including surviving an assassination attempt by House Hlaalu.', 'Lleril is a measured and diplomatic leader who approaches governance with wisdom and compassion. He demonstrates unwavering loyalty to House Redoran''s traditions while showing remarkable adaptability in facing Raven Rock''s modern challenges. Though proud of his heritage and position, he remains approachable and genuinely concerned for his people''s welfare, balancing authority with kindness.', 'A dignified Dunmer male with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, carrying himself with the proper bearing of Redoran nobility. His features show signs of age and the wisdom that comes with years of leadership, while his posture remains straight and proud despite the burdens of his position.', '* Adril Arano - Trusted Second Councilor and close friend who assists in governing Raven Rock * Cindiri Arano - Wife of Adril, part of his inner circle * House Hlaalu - Enemies who plotted his assassination * Brara Morvayn - His deceased mother and predecessor as Councilor * Citizens of Raven Rock - Maintains a caring but formal relationship with his subjects', 'Lleril serves as the House Redoran Councilor of Raven Rock and the primary authority figure on Solstheim. His responsibilities include managing the settlement''s affairs, representing House Redoran''s interests, and working to maintain order and prosperity despite limited resources. He holds court daily in Morvayn Manor, where he addresses the concerns of citizens and handles administrative duties.', '* Experienced diplomat and negotiator * Knowledgeable in House Redoran law and traditions * Competent swordsman, as evidenced by his carrying an elven sword * Administrative and leadership expertise * Political acumen and strategic thinking', 'Speaks with formal eloquence and careful consideration, employing diplomatic language that reflects his noble upbringing and position. His tone is authoritative yet welcoming, often using traditional Dunmer honorifics and formal modes of address.', '* Restore Raven Rock to its former prosperity and glory * Maintain House Redoran''s influence and traditions on Solstheim * Protect his people from threats both internal and external * Secure the successful operation of the reopened ebony mines * Strengthen diplomatic ties with other political entities while maintaining autonomy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('llewellyn_the_nightingale', 'Llewellyn the Nightingale is a skilled Nord bard whose musical talents and storytelling abilities have earned him a respected position at Lakeview Manor. Beyond his cheerful demeanor lies a passionate artist who has dedicated his life to preserving and performing the rich oral traditions of Skyrim, earning his nickname through his particularly melodious voice.', 'nord, bard, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Llewellyn received his formal training at the Bards College in Solitude, where he excelled in both musical performance and historical storytelling. After graduating, he spent several years traveling across Skyrim''s holds, collecting local tales and perfecting his craft before settling into service at Lakeview Manor.', 'Llewellyn is characterized by his unwavering optimism and genuine enthusiasm for his art, approaching each performance with the same dedication whether playing for nobles or common folk. He maintains a professional yet warm relationship with his employers, showing particular loyalty to those who appreciate his talents, while his forgiving nature allows him to maintain positive relationships even through difficult circumstances.', 'A typical Nord of average height and sturdy build, Llewellyn carries himself with the practiced posture of a performer. His face bears the weathered look of someone who has spent many years traveling Skyrim''s roads, though his eyes retain a youthful sparkle that matches his cheerful disposition.', '* The Dragonborn - Employer and patron, whom he serves with loyalty and respect * Lakeview Manor Steward - Professional colleague and fellow servant * Bards College - Maintains connections with his alma mater and fellow graduates * Local tavern keepers - Network of professional contacts from his traveling days', 'As the resident bard of Lakeview Manor, Llewellyn provides entertainment through music and storytelling while helping maintain the cultural atmosphere of the household. His duties include performing traditional Nordic ballads, reciting historical tales, and composing new pieces to commemorate significant events in the household.', '* Masterful singing voice, particularly suited to traditional Nordic ballads * Accomplished lute and drum player * Expert knowledge of Skyrim''s oral traditions and historical tales * Skilled composer capable of creating original works * Professional-level storytelling and public speaking abilities', 'Llewellyn speaks with the refined diction of a trained performer, often incorporating poetic phrases and musical cadences into his everyday speech. His voice carries the distinct accent of a Nord, but with the polished edge that comes from formal bardic training.', '* Preserve and pass on the traditional songs and stories of Skyrim * Compose memorable works that will outlive him and be performed by future generations * Build a reputation as one of Skyrim''s most accomplished bards * Create a collection of original ballads chronicling the great deeds of his patron');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lob', 'Lob is a dedicated Orc ranger and apprentice craftsman at the Largashbur stronghold, learning the arts of metalworking and community service under the tutelage of Garakh. Despite the curse afflicting his home, he maintains unwavering devotion to Malacath and his duties, while harboring aspirations to become a respected craftsman within the stronghold.', 'orc, archer, rift, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Largashbur, Lob grew up during a period when the stronghold was already under Malacath''s curse. Despite the hardships, he was taken under Garakh''s wing at a young age, where he began learning the essential skills needed to maintain the stronghold''s infrastructure and craft weapons worthy of Malacath''s followers.', 'Lob is hardworking and devoted to both his duties and faith in Malacath, showing remarkable persistence even in the face of the stronghold''s difficulties. He displays a humble eagerness to learn and improve his crafting skills, combined with a strong sense of responsibility towards his community''s wellbeing.', 'Like most male Orcs, Lob has a powerful, muscular build suited to both physical labor and combat. His skin bears the typical green hue of his race, with prominent tusks and the characteristic robust bone structure of Orsimer.', '* Garakh - Mentor and teacher in metalworking and stronghold maintenance * Chief Yamarz - Tribal leader whom he serves with loyalty despite the curse * Other Largashbur residents - Fellow community members he supports through his daily work * Malacath - Revered deity whom he strives to please through his craftsmanship', 'Lob serves multiple roles within Largashbur, primarily as a ranger responsible for livestock management and stronghold maintenance. He is also an apprentice metalworker, learning the craft to eventually take Garakh''s place as the stronghold''s primary craftsman.', '* Proficient in animal husbandry and livestock management * Developing expertise in metalworking and weapon crafting * Capable warrior skilled with one-handed weapons, particularly war axes * Practical knowledge of stronghold maintenance and repair', 'Lob speaks with the direct, straightforward manner typical of Orcs, often referencing Malacath and expressing determination to improve his craft. His speech reflects both his religious devotion and his practical mindset.', '* Master the art of metalworking to create weapons worthy of Malacath''s approval * Successfully take over Garakh''s position as the stronghold''s master craftsman * Help lift the curse affecting Largashbur and restore the stronghold''s prosperity * Prove himself as a valuable member of the stronghold community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lod', 'Lod is a skilled Nord blacksmith in Falkreath who exemplifies the Nordic values of loyalty and honor through his unwavering dedication to the former Jarl Dengeir of Stuhn. Despite personally wishing for peace, he continues forging weapons for the Imperial Legion out of a complex sense of duty that balances his loyalty to both Dengeir and the Empire.', 'nord, blacksmith, falkreath, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath, Lod served as Dengeir''s personal guard for many years, risking his life multiple times to protect the former Jarl. His expertise in smithing and unwavering loyalty earned him his position as the town''s primary blacksmith, though the political shifts in Falkreath have placed him in a delicate position between his old loyalties and current obligations.', 'Lod is characterized by his strong sense of honor and steadfast loyalty, particularly to those who have earned his respect. He shows a philosophical awareness of the war''s toll on Skyrim, expressing weariness of the bloodshed while continuing to fulfill his duties. Though practical in his work, he places personal bonds and loyalty above material gain.', 'A sturdy Nord with the muscular build typical of a career blacksmith, weathered by years of working the forge. His hands are calloused from countless hours of metalworking, and his face bears the marks of age and experience working in the heat of the forge.', '* Dengeir of Stuhn - Former Jarl and close friend whom he served as personal guard * Siddgeir - Current Jarl, maintains professional but distant relationship * Imperial Legion - Professional relationship as a weapons supplier * Falkreath Guards - Regular business contacts for weapon maintenance * Kust - Cemetery caretaker who seeks his help in obtaining books', 'Lod serves as Falkreath''s primary blacksmith, crafting weapons and armor for both the town guard and the Imperial Legion. He maintains a forge and shop in the southern part of town, where he works tirelessly for twelve hours each day crafting and selling his wares.', '* Expert blacksmith capable of forging various weapons and armor * Experienced warrior from his time as Dengeir''s personal guard * Proficient in weapon maintenance and repair * Knowledge of Imperial Legion armor and weapon specifications * Basic combat skills with sword and shield', 'Lod speaks with the direct, honest manner typical of Nord craftsmen, often incorporating references to steel and loyalty in his conversations. His speech reflects his philosophical nature, frequently making observations about the state of Skyrim and the impact of the civil war.', '* Maintain his forge and continue serving Falkreath''s smithing needs * Honor his loyalty to both Dengeir and the Empire without compromising his principles * See an end to the civil war while fulfilling his duties * Find the stray dog he''s heard about on the roads (immediate goal) * Preserve the traditional Nordic values of loyalty and honor in changing times');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lodi', 'Lodi is a talented Nord bard specializing in flute performance, temporarily employed to provide music at Vittoria Vici''s ill-fated wedding in Solitude. Known for his intense focus and dedication to his craft, he represents the professional musicianship cultivated by the Bards College, though his involvement in the tragic wedding ceremony would leave a lasting mark on his career.', 'nord, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Trained at the prestigious Bards College in Solitude, Lodi developed his musical talents under the guidance of experienced instructors like Pantea Ateia. His exceptional skill with the flute earned him recognition among Solitude''s elite, leading to his selection as one of the performers at Vittoria Vici''s high-profile wedding. Though his early life remains largely unknown, his refined manner and education suggest a background that afforded him proper musical training.', 'Lodi exhibits intense focus and dedication to his craft, often to the point of appearing antisocial when performing. His professional demeanor masks an underlying sensitivity, as evidenced by his strong emotional reaction to violence at the wedding. He shows signs of being somewhat high-strung and perfectionist in his work, prioritizing flawless performance over social interaction.', 'A typical Nord male with the strong build characteristic of his race, though perhaps slightly less muscular due to his artistic pursuits rather than martial training. His hands show the refined dexterity of a skilled musician, with long fingers well-suited to playing the flute. His posture while performing suggests years of practiced discipline.', '* Pantea Ateia - Mentor and fellow performer at the Bards College * Vittoria Vici - Wealthy client who hired him for her wedding * Bards College - Professional affiliation as a graduate and occasional performer * Solitude''s Noble Families - Regular clients for various social events', 'Professional bard specializing in flute performance, primarily serving at high-society events in Solitude. His position as a wedding musician for prominent nobles indicates his respected status within the musical community, though he also likely performs at other significant social gatherings throughout the city.', '* Master-level flutist with exceptional breath control and finger dexterity * Formal musical education and theory from the Bards College * Professional event performance experience * Basic knowledge of court etiquette and noble customs', 'Speaks with the refined accent of an educated Nord, using proper grammar and maintaining a professional, somewhat distant tone. His responses are typically brief and focused on his immediate task, reflecting his prioritization of his performance duties.', '* Maintain his reputation as a respected professional musician in Solitude * Distance himself from the tragic events of Vittoria Vici''s wedding * Continue developing his musical abilities * Secure stable employment through noble patronage');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lodvar', 'Lodvar is a hardworking Nord lumberjack living in Dragon Bridge who maintains a gruff, standoffish exterior while harboring deep romantic feelings for his sister-in-law Olda. His daily life is dominated by manual labor at his brother''s mill, where underlying tensions simmer regarding their business''s financial state.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Dragon Bridge, Lodvar grew up learning the lumber trade alongside his brother Horgeir, eventually becoming an integral part of the family business. While his brother married and established himself as the mill owner, Lodvar remained single and somewhat resentful, developing an unrequited attraction to his brother''s wife while becoming increasingly concerned about their business''s financial stability.', 'Lodvar presents himself as a stern, antisocial worker who rebuffs strangers and refuses to offer charity, likely stemming from his concerns about their financial situation. Beneath this harsh exterior lies a surprisingly romantic and sensitive soul, particularly evident in his interactions with Olda, though his attraction to his brother''s wife suggests possible difficulties with maintaining appropriate boundaries.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the muscular build typical of someone who performs heavy manual labor daily. His hands are calloused from years of handling lumber, and his face likely shows the weathering effects of working outdoors year-round.', '* Horgeir - Brother and employer, relationship strained by business disagreements and Lodvar''s feelings for Olda * Olda - Sister-in-law for whom he harbors romantic feelings, creating underlying tension * Dragon Bridge residents - Maintains minimal social connections, preferring to keep to himself', 'Lodvar works as a lumberjack at his brother''s mill, spending long hours loading and managing logs for processing. His position is both physical laborer and unofficial business partner, though he lacks actual ownership stake in the operation.', '* Experienced lumberjack capable of handling heavy logs and operating mill equipment * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Knowledge of wood processing and lumber industry operations * Cooking skills sufficient for basic meal preparation', 'Lodvar speaks in short, direct sentences, often dismissive or curt with strangers while showing a softer, more eloquent side when speaking with Olda. His vocabulary and tone reflect his working-class background, but he can be surprisingly articulate when discussing romantic matters.', '* Find a romantic partner similar to Olda, though his fixation on her specifically may hinder this goal * Resolve the financial concerns he perceives in the family business * Maintain his position at the mill while preserving family relationships despite underlying tensions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('logrolf_the_willful', 'Logrolf the Willful is an elderly but formidable Nord priest who deliberately provokes the Daedric Prince Molag Bal by performing Boethiah''s rituals in his abandoned shrine. His defiant nature and unwavering dedication to Boethiah showcase his fearless commitment to challenging divine powers, even at great personal risk.', 'nord, priest, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Logrolf discovered his calling as a priest of Boethiah in his younger years after witnessing the Daedric Prince''s influence in a power struggle. He spent decades studying Daedric lore and performing increasingly bold acts of defiance against Boethiah''s rivals, eventually settling in Markarth to conduct his most daring spiritual provocation yet.', 'Logrolf is extraordinarily stubborn and confrontational, taking pride in his ability to resist and mock powerful entities. He exhibits a zealot''s dedication to Boethiah''s principles of treachery and conflict, actively seeking ways to create strife and challenge established powers. Despite his advanced age, he maintains an intimidating presence through his sharp tongue and unflinching resolve.', 'A weathered Nord of advanced years with deep-set eyes and pronounced facial wrinkles that speak to decades of hardship. Despite his age, he maintains a straight-backed, proud bearing and moves with surprising vigor. His face bears ritual scarification marks typical of devoted Boethiah cultists.', '* Boethiah - Devoted follower and willing agent of chaos * Molag Bal - Sworn enemy whom he deliberately provokes and defies * Vigilants of Stendarr - Active opponents who seek to stop his Daedric worship * Local Markarth citizens - Maintain distance due to his mysterious and unsettling presence', 'Logrolf serves as a rogue priest of Boethiah, conducting unauthorized rituals and spreading his deity''s influence through acts of defiance and conflict. He maintains no formal position within Markarth''s religious hierarchy, operating independently from an abandoned house that serves as both his home and ritual space.', '* Expert in Daedric rituals and occult practices * Proficient in Destruction magic, particularly spells causing pain and suffering * Skilled in theological debate and religious rhetoric * Remarkable resistance to physical and psychological torture * Advanced knowledge of Daedric artifacts and their powers', 'Speaks with a commanding, deliberately provocative tone, often employing religious terminology and archaic phrasings. His speech is marked by frequent taunts and challenges, particularly when addressing those he considers servants of rival powers.', '* Prove his ultimate loyalty to Boethiah through continued defiance of Molag Bal * Establish a permanent shrine to Boethiah within Molag Bal''s sphere of influence * Inspire others to challenge divine authority through his example of unwavering defiance * Achieve a memorable death that would please Boethiah and mock her rivals');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lokil', 'Lokil is a high-ranking Nord vampire in service to Lord Harkon, tasked with uncovering the ancient artifact hidden within Dimhollow Crypt. As a ruthless and methodical commander, he leads a group of vampires in their mission while demonstrating both tactical intelligence and unwavering loyalty to his master''s cause.', 'nord, mage, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally a Nord warrior who was turned into a vampire by Harkon''s court, Lokil rose through the ranks of the Volkihar clan through his exceptional dedication and ruthlessness. His proven ability to command and strategic mind earned him the trust of Lord Harkon, leading to his appointment as leader of the Dimhollow expedition. His ambitions and competence have made him a rival to other prominent vampires in Harkon''s court, particularly Vingalmo and Orthjolf.', 'Lokil exhibits a cold, calculating demeanor typical of master vampires, showing no mercy to his enemies while maintaining unwavering loyalty to those he considers allies. His interrogation of Vigilant Adalvald demonstrates both his patience and brutality, while his political maneuvering within Harkon''s court reveals his ambitious nature. He values loyalty above all else, keeping careful track of both friends and enemies.', 'As a Nord vampire, Lokil possesses the characteristic pale skin and glowing eyes of his kind, with sharp facial features twisted by his vampiric nature. His powerful build reflects his Nordic warrior heritage, though transformed by the gaunt, predatory aspects of vampirism. His face bears the ancient, aristocratic features common to master vampires of Harkon''s court.', '* Lord Harkon - Supreme master whom he serves with absolute loyalty * Vingalmo and Orthjolf - Rivals within Harkon''s court whom he seeks to supersede * Vigilants of Stendarr - Enemies he views with contempt and uses for information * Subordinate vampires - Maintains strict authority over lesser vampires under his command', 'Lokil serves as a high-ranking commander within Lord Harkon''s vampire court, specifically leading the mission to uncover the artifact in Dimhollow Crypt. His position places him above common vampires but below Harkon''s inner circle, though he actively works to advance his standing.', '* Master-level destruction magic specialized in frost spells * Advanced vampire powers including life drain and supernatural strength * Exceptional combat abilities honed through centuries of experience * Strategic military leadership and tactical planning * Skilled interrogator and intelligence gatherer', 'Lokil speaks with the cold, aristocratic tone common to master vampires, employing formal language that reflects his elevated status within vampire society. His speech patterns reveal both his Nordic heritage and centuries of existence in Harkon''s court, combining warrior''s directness with vampiric sophistication.', '* Uncover and retrieve the artifact hidden within Dimhollow Crypt * Advance his position within Harkon''s court by superseding Vingalmo and Orthjolf * Prove his worth to Lord Harkon through successful completion of his mission * Expand his influence and power within vampire society');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lokir', 'Lokir is a desperate Nord thief from Rorikstead who meets his end during the opening scenes of Skyrim. A common criminal caught in extraordinary circumstances, he represents the ordinary citizen whose life is upended by the civil war, ultimately dying in a futile attempt to escape execution.', 'nord, thief, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born and raised in the farming community of Rorikstead, Lokir turned to thievery rather than honest labor. His final crime was stealing a horse near the Skyrim border, inadvertently becoming entangled in an Imperial ambush meant for Ulfric Stormcloak and his rebels.', 'Lokir is cowardly, selfish, and prone to panic under pressure. He constantly tries to distance himself from the Stormcloaks and shows no dignity in the face of death, contrasting sharply with the stoic Nordic warrior stereotype. His behavior suggests a person accustomed to talking or running his way out of trouble rather than facing consequences.', 'A typical Nord male with the characteristic hardy build of his race, though likely less muscular than warriors or farmers. His appearance suggests a life of avoiding direct confrontation rather than engaging in physical labor or combat.', '* Imperial Legion - Adversarial relationship as his captors * Stormcloaks - Antagonistic, blames them for his predicament * Rorikstead Community - Likely strained relationships due to his criminal activities * Fellow Prisoners - Brief connection through shared fate, though he attempts to distance himself', 'Lokir is a thief operating in the Whiterun Hold region, primarily targeting travelers and isolated settlements. His attempt to steal a horse suggests he may have worked as a horse thief specifically, targeting the valuable animals from Skyrim''s stables and farms.', '* Experienced horse thief with knowledge of handling and stealing horses * Some capability in stealth and evasion tactics * Basic survival skills necessary for life as a criminal * Likely knowledge of Skyrim''s roads and escape routes', 'Speaks with a panicked, desperate tone marked by frequent exclamations and pleas. His dialect is that of a common Nord, but his voice often breaks with fear, especially when addressing authority figures.', '* Immediate survival and escape from Imperial custody * Avoid execution by convincing authorities he''s not associated with the Stormcloaks * Potentially flee to Hammerfell to escape prosecution');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lond', 'Lond Northstrider is a dedicated Nord miner who has made the Quicksilver Mine in Dawnstar his true home, working tirelessly without rest or complaint. His unwavering work ethic and simple outlook on life make him a stabilizing presence amidst the drama of his workplace, particularly the bitter feud between his employer Leigelf and Beitild.', 'nord, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Lond has spent his entire life working in mines, eventually finding his permanent home in Dawnstar''s Quicksilver Mine. Originally intended to share living quarters with fellow miner Fruki, he instead chose to make the mine itself his permanent residence, reflecting his complete devotion to his work. His surname ''Northstrider'' suggests a family history of exploring or working in Skyrim''s harsh northern regions.', 'Lond is the epitome of a simple, hardworking Nord who finds contentment in routine and physical labor. He demonstrates remarkable emotional stability and logical thinking, often serving as a voice of reason to his emotionally volatile employer Leigelf. His straightforward nature and unwavering loyalty make him a dependable presence in the mine, though his complete devotion to work borders on concerning obsession.', 'Lond has the sturdy build typical of Nord miners, with well-developed muscles from years of continuous physical labor. His hands are calloused and strong from countless hours wielding a pickaxe, and his skin shows the weathered quality common to those who work both outdoors and in the mines. His appearance reflects his tireless work ethic, with visible signs of exhaustion that never seem to slow him down.', '* Leigelf - Employer and friend whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Fruki - Fellow miner with whom he was meant to share living quarters * Beitild - His boss''s estranged wife, owner of the rival Iron-Breaker Mine * Other Dawnstar miners - Maintains professional working relationships', 'Lond serves as a senior miner at the Quicksilver Mine, operating both as a traditional miner and smelter operator. His role involves extracting quicksilver ore during night shifts and processing it at the smelter during daylight hours, effectively doing the work of two men without rest.', '* Expert in mining techniques and ore extraction * Highly skilled at operating smelting equipment * Exceptional physical endurance and strength from constant labor * Basic knowledge of metallurgy and ore processing * Experienced in quicksilver handling and refinement', 'Lond speaks in short, direct sentences, avoiding unnecessary elaboration or emotional language. His manner of speech reflects his straightforward nature, often stating facts plainly and without embellishment.', '* Maintain the success and operation of Quicksilver Mine * Support Leigelf in his ongoing business rivalry with Beitild * Continue his simple but fulfilling life of honest work * Find relief from the nightmares plaguing Dawnstar''s residents');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lortheim', 'Lortheim is a devoted Nord priest who serves at Windhelm''s Temple of Talos, maintaining unwavering faith despite the Empire''s ban on Talos worship. As a spiritual leader in the stronghold of the Stormcloak rebellion, he represents the religious resistance against Imperial religious suppression while providing guidance and comfort to those who still follow the Nine Divines.', 'nord, priest, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Lortheim dedicated his life to the priesthood from an early age, studying the teachings of Talos under the older generation of priests. He witnessed firsthand the devastating impact of the White-Gold Concordat and the subsequent ban on Talos worship, choosing to remain in Windhelm where he could continue his religious duties openly under Ulfric Stormcloak''s protection.', 'Lortheim is a calm, wise, and deeply spiritual individual who maintains his religious conviction without becoming militant or aggressive. Despite the persecution of his faith, he remains optimistic about the future while showing remarkable courage in continuing his religious duties openly. He approaches his role with both dignity and humility, viewing the current political conflict through a religious lens.', 'A mature Nord man with the weathered features typical of those who have spent their lives in Skyrim''s harsh climate. His bearing is dignified and priestly, with the straight posture and measured movements of one accustomed to performing religious ceremonies.', '* Jora - His devoted wife and fellow priest at the Temple of Talos * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respects him as a protector of Talos worship * Temple Worshippers - Serves as their spiritual guide and counselor * Imperial Authority - Maintains peaceful resistance against their religious restrictions', 'Lortheim serves as a priest at the Temple of Talos in Windhelm, performing religious ceremonies, offering blessings, and providing spiritual guidance to worshippers. He maintains the temple alongside his wife Jora, ensuring it remains a sanctuary for those who wish to worship Talos despite the Empire''s ban.', '* Extensive knowledge of religious doctrine and Talos worship * Accomplished public speaker and spiritual counselor * Basic restoration magic typical of Nord priests * Ceremonial rites and religious ritual expertise', 'Speaks with formal, measured tones befitting his station as a priest, often incorporating religious references and blessings into his speech. His manner of speaking reflects both his education and his role as a religious authority figure.', '* Preserve the worship of Talos despite Imperial prohibition * Guide and protect his congregation through troubled times * Witness the day when Talos worship is once again freely practiced throughout Skyrim * Maintain the Temple as a beacon of hope for true believers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('louis_letrush', 'Louis Letrush is a cunning Breton bard and horse enthusiast who operates within Riften''s shadowy business circles, particularly known for his attempted dealings with the influential Black-Briar family. A smooth-talking opportunist with refined tastes despite his modest appearance, he specializes in brokering deals and manipulating others to achieve his ends.', 'breton, bard, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Letrush made his way to Skyrim seeking opportunities in the province''s lucrative horse trade and merchant circles. He established himself in Riften, using his bardic talents and silver tongue to navigate the city''s criminal underbelly while maintaining a legitimate facade. His most ambitious venture involved attempting to purchase Frost, one of Skyrim''s finest breeding horses, from Sibbi Black-Briar.', 'Letrush is a calculating opportunist who carefully weighs risks and rewards, preferring to use others to do his dirty work while maintaining plausible deniability. He exhibits sophisticated tastes and mannerisms that belie his modest appearance, suggesting a background of some refinement. Though generally cordial, he shows a notable aversion to authority figures and carefully maintains a network of contacts through charm and manipulation.', 'A well-groomed Breton of average height with sharp, observant features typical of his race. Despite his lower-class attire, he maintains an immaculate appearance with clean-cut hair and proper posture that suggests noble breeding or education. His hands show signs of a life of leisure rather than manual labor.', '* Sibbi Black-Briar - Business associate turned adversary after a failed horse purchase deal * Maven Black-Briar - Powerful figure he carefully avoids directly crossing * Riften''s Criminal Underground - Various contacts and connections he maintains * The Bee and Barb Staff - Regular establishment contacts who tolerate his constant presence', 'Officially a bard by trade, though this serves primarily as a cover for his true activities as a wheeler-dealer and horse trader. He specializes in brokering deals and arranging transactions, particularly in Riften''s grey market, while maintaining enough legitimate business to avoid unwanted attention.', '* Expert in persuasion and negotiation tactics * Knowledgeable about horses, particularly breeding lineages * Proficient in gathering information and maintaining useful contacts * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Musical talent as a bard, though rarely demonstrated', 'Speaks in a refined, articulate manner with careful word choice and subtle manipulation woven into his dialogue. His tone remains consistently smooth and controlled, regardless of circumstances, with hints of a High Rock accent.', '* Acquire valuable breeding horses, particularly Frost, to establish himself in Skyrim''s horse trade * Build enough wealth and influence to secure a position of respect in Riften''s business community * Maintain independence from the Black-Briars while avoiding their direct enmity * Eventually establish his own horse breeding operation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lowlife', 'Lowlife is a hardened Nord bandit who has carved out a niche in Riften''s notorious Ratway, where he preys on trespassers and unfortunate wanderers who stray into his territory. A product of Skyrim''s harsh criminal underworld, he represents the dangerous elements that lurk in the city''s shadows, serving as both predator and territorial guardian of the underground maze.', 'nord, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born to a poor family in Riften''s waterfront district, Lowlife grew up learning to survive through petty theft and violence. After several stints in the Riften jail as a youth, he found his true calling among the desperate outcasts of the Ratway, where his aggressive nature and survival instincts made him a natural fit for bandit life.', 'Lowlife is an aggressive and territorial individual who attacks first and asks questions never. Years of living in the Ratway have made him deeply paranoid and quick to violence, viewing any intruders as potential threats or prey. He takes a perverse pride in his role as one of the Ratway''s feared denizens.', 'A weathered Nord male in his late thirties, Lowlife bears numerous scars from years of violent encounters. His face is gaunt and angular, with deep-set eyes and a perpetual scowl, while his muscular build reflects the physical demands of his predatory lifestyle.', '* Fellow Ratway Bandits - Loose alliance of convenience and mutual protection * Riften Guard - Hostile relationship marked by occasional violent encounters * Thieves Guild - Uneasy coexistence, generally avoiding direct conflict * Ratway Vagrants - Potential victims and occasional informants', 'Lowlife operates as a bandit within the Ratway, making his living through robbery, extortion, and violence against those who venture into his territory. He maintains an informal role as one of the many self-appointed ''gatekeepers'' of the Ratway''s dangerous passages.', '* Proficient in close-quarters combat, especially in the confined spaces of the Ratway * Experienced in ambush tactics and territorial defense * Skilled at intimidation and threatening behavior * Basic lockpicking abilities for accessing hidden areas and loot', 'Speaks in a rough, aggressive manner with frequent threats and crude language. His voice carries a harsh Riften accent typical of the city''s criminal element.', '* Maintain and expand his territory within the Ratway * Accumulate wealth through robbery and extortion * Survive and thrive in the harsh underground environment * Avoid capture by the Riften guard while maintaining his predatory lifestyle');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lu''ah_al-skaven', 'Lu''ah Al-Skaven is a grief-stricken Redguard conjurer whose descent into necromancy began after losing her husband Saeel in the Civil War. Once a respected mage, she now commands an army of draugr from within Ansilvund, driven by a desperate mission to resurrect her beloved husband and exact vengeance on those who perpetuate Skyrim''s conflicts.', 'redguard, mage, eastmarch, legion', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally a talented conjuration mage from Hammerfell, Lu''ah married a fellow Redguard named Saeel who served in the Imperial Legion. After his death in the Civil War, she became obsessed with soul manipulation and necromancy, eventually discovering the ancient Nordic tomb of Ansilvund. She took residence there, conducting increasingly dangerous experiments while raising draugr to serve her growing vendetta against both sides of the war.', 'Lu''ah is consumed by grief and bitterness, having allowed her loss to transform her from a rational scholar into an vengeful necromancer. She displays signs of mental instability, talking to herself and her deceased husband, yet maintains enough lucidity to orchestrate complex magical rituals and command her undead forces. Despite her descent into darkness, she still holds onto the love for her husband that drives her actions.', 'Lu''ah is a middle-aged Redguard woman with sharp features and dark skin marked by the stress of her obsessive research. Her once-athletic frame has become gaunt from years of isolation and magical experimentation, while her eyes carry an unnatural glow from prolonged exposure to necromantic energies.', '* Saeel - Beloved husband whose death in service to the Empire drove her to necromancy * Imperial Legion - Former allies turned enemies after they sent Saeel to his death * Stormcloaks - Viewed as equally responsible for the meaningless conflict that widowed her * Draugr - Undead servants she has raised to form her army * Local Nords - Fearful of her presence and the desecration of their ancestral tomb', 'Lu''ah serves as the self-appointed master of Ansilvund, conducting necromantic research and commanding an army of draugr. She has transformed from a respected mage into a dreaded necromancer, devoting herself entirely to the pursuit of resurrection magic and vengeance.', '* Master-level conjuration magic with expertise in necromancy and soul manipulation * Powerful control over draugr and other undead entities * Advanced knowledge of ancient Nordic burial rites and customs * Skilled researcher with extensive understanding of soul transfer magic * Capable of maintaining magical control over an entire dungeon''s worth of undead simultaneously', 'Lu''ah speaks with an authoritative and threatening tone, her voice echoing unnaturally through Ansilvund''s chambers. Her speech patterns alternate between rational academic discourse and emotional outbursts, particularly when discussing her husband or the war.', '* Successfully resurrect her husband Saeel through advanced necromantic rituals * Take revenge on both sides of the Civil War for their role in her husband''s death * Build an unstoppable army of draugr to enforce her will across Skyrim * Perfect the art of soul transfer to achieve true resurrection, not mere reanimation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('luaffyn', 'Luaffyn is a talented Dark Elf bard who has found refuge in Windhelm''s Candlehearth Hall, using her musical gifts to carve out a peaceful existence despite the city''s notorious prejudice against her kind. Through her melodic performances and gentle demeanor, she works to bridge cultural divides and bring moments of joy to the tavern''s patrons, while quietly preserving Dunmer musical traditions far from her homeland.', 'darkelf, bard, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Luaffyn learned the ancient songs and musical traditions of her people from an early age. Following the Red Mountain''s eruption and the subsequent Dunmer exodus, she made her way to Skyrim, eventually settling in Windhelm where her talent for music helped her secure a position at Candlehearth Hall despite the local Nordic prejudice against Dark Elves.', 'Luaffyn maintains a dignified and graceful demeanor despite the challenging social climate for Dunmer in Windhelm. She is introspective and observant, using music as both a shield and a bridge between cultures, while carefully navigating the complex racial tensions in the city. Her calm and measured approach to adversity reveals inner strength beneath her gentle exterior.', 'Luaffyn has the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her Dunmer heritage, with delicate features that often display a serene expression. Her frame is slight but graceful, with the natural elegance typical of elven kind. Her movements are measured and deliberate, reflecting years of practiced performance.', '* Elda Early-Dawn - Employer and owner of Candlehearth Hall who values her talent despite local prejudices * Susanna the Wicked - Fellow employee and friendly colleague * Malthyr Elenil - Friend and confidant from the Gray Quarter * Revyn Sadri - Regular patron who appreciates her preservation of Dunmer musical traditions', 'Luaffyn serves as the primary bard of Candlehearth Hall, performing traditional Nordic ballads alongside subtle incorporations of Dunmer musical elements. Her duties include nightly performances in the upper level of the tavern, where she works to maintain a welcoming atmosphere for all patrons through her carefully chosen repertoire.', '* Accomplished vocalist trained in both Nordic and Dunmer musical traditions * Skilled lute player with expertise in multiple regional styles * Diplomatic ability to read audiences and adjust performances accordingly * Basic knowledge of restoration magic for self-preservation * Practiced storyteller with extensive knowledge of both Nordic and Dunmer folklore', 'Luaffyn speaks in a melodious, well-modulated voice that reflects her musical training, with the slight accent characteristic of Morrowind natives. She chooses her words carefully and maintains a formal, professional tone while remaining warm and approachable.', '* Maintain a successful and stable life in Windhelm despite the challenging political climate * Preserve and share Dunmer musical traditions while adapting to Nordic culture * Eventually earn enough money to open her own music school that would welcome students of all races * Help foster better understanding between Nords and Dunmer through the universal language of music');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lucan_valerius', 'Lucan Valerius is a pragmatic Imperial merchant who runs the Riverwood Trader, demonstrating both business acumen and cautious determination in the face of adversity. Despite suffering a significant theft, he maintains his commercial presence in Riverwood while showing shrewd judgment in delegating dangerous tasks to capable adventurers.', 'imperial, merchant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Lucan established himself in Riverwood with his sister Camilla, building the Riverwood Trader into a respectable establishment. His possession of the Golden Claw suggests either inheritance or acquisition through his merchant dealings, though the true story behind how he obtained this ancient Nordic artifact remains untold.', 'Lucan is cautious and practical, preferring to solve problems through delegation rather than personal risk. He displays a protective nature toward both his business interests and his sister Camilla, though this sometimes manifests as stubborn inflexibility. While generally honest in his dealings, he maintains a merchant''s shrewdness in all transactions.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the typical olive complexion of his race, showing signs of a life spent indoors managing his shop. His hands bear the calluses of regularly handling merchandise, while his posture reflects someone accustomed to standing behind a counter for long hours.', '* Camilla Valerius - Younger sister and shop assistant, whom he''s protective of but sometimes controlling towards * Sven - Views him with suspicion due to his interest in Camilla * Faendal - Maintains neutral business relations despite his pursuit of Camilla * Local Riverwood residents - Generally positive business relationships * Arvel the Swift - Enemy who stole his prized Golden Claw', 'Owner and proprietor of the Riverwood Trader, managing day-to-day operations including buying, selling, and trading various goods. His position makes him one of the more prominent merchants in Riverwood, serving as a vital commercial hub for the small community.', '* Experienced merchant with strong bartering and negotiation abilities * Practical knowledge of various goods and their market values * Basic weapon proficiency with iron dagger and mace for self-defense * Fundamental business management and bookkeeping expertise', 'Speaks in a direct, business-like manner with the refined accent typical of Cyrodiil natives. His tone often carries an underlying cautious note, particularly when discussing matters related to his shop or sister.', '* Maintain and expand the success of the Riverwood Trader * Protect his sister Camilla while ensuring she remains to help with the family business * Recover and preserve valuable artifacts like the Golden Claw * Establish himself as the preeminent merchant in Riverwood');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lucky_lorenz', 'Lucky Lorenz was a solitary Nord bandit who lived in a modest shack along the White River, known for his ironic nickname and tragic demise. Despite his outlaw status, he maintained an appreciation for literature and religious devotion, suggesting a more complex character than the typical bandit.', 'nord, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malebandit', '', 'Born to unknown parents in Skyrim, Lorenz likely turned to banditry after failing to establish a legitimate life for himself. He chose a relatively isolated existence, setting up his home away from major settlements while presumably conducting raids on travelers along the White River. His nickname ''Lucky'' was possibly earned through successfully evading capture or surviving dangerous situations, making his death by falling tree particularly ironic.', 'Based on his possessions and living arrangements, Lorenz appears to have been a cultured bandit with refined tastes despite his criminal lifestyle. His devotion to Dibella and choice of reading material suggest he was a romantic at heart, while his solitary lifestyle indicates he may have been more introspective than the typical bandit. His decision to live alone rather than join a larger bandit group hints at an independent streak and possible disdain for the more brutal aspects of bandit life.', 'As a Nord male, Lorenz would have possessed the typically robust build and hardy constitution of his race. His lifestyle as a bandit would have left him physically fit and weather-worn from living in the harsh Skyrim wilderness. His body, though crushed, suggests he was of average height for a Nord male.', '* Local Bandits - Likely maintained loose connections for information and trade * Merchants - Probable fence contacts for selling stolen goods * Dibella - Religious devotion evidenced by shrine in his home * White River Residents - Potential victims of his bandit activities', 'Lorenz operated as an independent bandit, likely targeting travelers along the White River trade routes. Unlike many bandits who operate in groups, he preferred to work alone, suggesting he may have specialized in stealth and cunning rather than brute force.', '* Proficient in stealth and ambush tactics for solo banditry * Capable swimmer and navigator of river territories * Basic survival skills including hunting and foraging * Literate and cultured, unusual for a common bandit * Light armor expertise, as evidenced by his reading material', 'Given his literacy and apparent sophistication, Lorenz likely spoke with more refinement than typical bandits, though still retaining a Nordic accent. His speech probably reflected his dual nature as both an outlaw and an educated man.', '* Accumulate enough wealth to potentially retire from banditry * Maintain independence while avoiding detection by guards * Further his devotion to Dibella through study and worship * Build a more comfortable life along the White River');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lund', 'Lund was a reclusive Nord farmer who lived alone in a humble hilltop hut near Rorikstead, harboring a peculiar affinity for skeevers that he seemingly kept as pets. His tragic end, whether by accident or intention, left behind a scene that hints at a deeper story of loss and isolation.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally a simple farmer from the Whiterun Hold, Lund likely settled in his isolated homestead following the death of his wife, as evidenced by the grave marker outside his home. The silver ring atop the grave suggests he maintained a deep connection to his deceased spouse, leading him to choose a life of solitude away from civilization.', 'Lund appears to have been a deeply troubled individual who found unusual companionship in skeevers, possibly as a way to cope with his loneliness. His choice to live in isolation and the circumstances of his death suggest he struggled with depression and grief, though he maintained enough presence of mind to care for his unusual pets.', 'A typical Nord male with the weathered features common to Skyrim''s farming population. His body shows signs of the physical toll of solitary farm work, with calloused hands and a sturdy, labor-hardened frame.', '* Unknown Wife - Deceased spouse whose grave he tended regularly * Skeevers - Unusual companions he appeared to keep as pets * Rorikstead Residents - Maintained minimal contact with nearby townspeople', 'Lund worked as a subsistence farmer, maintaining a small homestead where he grew crops and lived off the land. His isolated location suggests he rarely traded with others, likely producing just enough to sustain himself.', '* Basic farming and agricultural knowledge * Animal handling, particularly with skeevers * Self-sufficient survival skills * Basic carpentry and home maintenance abilities', 'Based on his Nordic heritage and farmer background, Lund likely spoke with the characteristic accent of Whiterun Hold''s rural population, using simple, practical language typical of Skyrim''s farming community.', '* Maintain his solitary existence away from society * Honor the memory of his deceased wife * Care for his unusual skeever companions * Find peace in his isolation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lurbuk', 'Lurbuk is an optimistically delusional Orc bard who performs at the Moorside Inn in Morthal, widely considered the worst musician in all of Skyrim. Despite universal disdain for his lacking musical talents, he maintains an unshakeable belief in his destined path to greatness and fame across Tamriel.', 'orc, bard, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born to Orcish parents, Lurbuk rejected the traditional warrior culture of the Orsimer to pursue his passion for music and performance arts. Having studied briefly at the Bards College in Solitude before being asked to leave, he eventually settled in Morthal where the innkeeper Jonna reluctantly allows him to perform and lodge in exchange for payment.', 'Lurbuk exhibits boundless optimism and complete obliviousness to both criticism and his own lack of talent. He is theatrical and grandiose in his self-image, often speaking of himself in the third person and maintaining unwavering confidence despite constant rejection. Despite his poor reception, he shows remarkable resilience and determination in pursuing his artistic dreams.', 'A male Orc of average height and build for his race, Lurbuk lacks the imposing musculature typical of most Orsimer due to his dedication to the bardic arts rather than martial pursuits. His features are somewhat softer than most Orcs, though he still possesses the characteristic tusks and green skin of his race.', '* Jonna - Innkeeper who tolerates his presence solely for business reasons * Morthal Townsfolk - Collectively annoyed by his performances but generally avoid direct confrontation * Bards College - Former brief association ended in rejection * Dark Brotherhood - Eventually targets him for assassination due to his terrible performances', 'Lurbuk serves as the resident bard at the Moorside Inn, performing daily from dawn until late night despite his complete lack of musical talent. He considers himself a professional entertainer and aspiring famous musician, though his only paying work comes from his regular performances at the inn.', '* Basic instrumental ability, though severely lacking in actual musical talent * Moderate proficiency with an iron mace for self-defense * Notable endurance for performing long hours * Remarkable ability to maintain optimism in the face of constant criticism', 'Lurbuk speaks in an enthusiastic, theatrical manner, often referring to himself in the third person and using grandiose language to describe his performances and aspirations. His speech is marked by poetic attempts and impromptu rhyming, though these are typically as unpolished as his musical performances.', '* Achieve fame and recognition as a renowned bard throughout Tamriel * Win the hearts and admiration of Morthal''s townspeople through his performances * Compose songs that will be remembered and praised for all eternity * Prove his critics wrong and validate his chosen path as a musician');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lydia', 'Lydia is a steadfast Nord warrior who serves as housecarl to the Dragonborn after their appointment as Thane of Whiterun. She embodies the Nordic values of loyalty, duty, and combat prowess, dedicating herself fully to protecting her Thane with unwavering devotion and dry wit.', 'nord, warrior, noble, whiterun, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun, Lydia trained extensively under the Whiterun guard and proved herself worthy of becoming a housecarl through demonstrated combat skill and loyalty to the hold. She was personally selected by Jarl Balgruuf to serve as housecarl to the newly appointed Thane, a position she accepts with both pride and humility.', 'Lydia is characterized by her stoic demeanor and sardonic sense of humor, often making dry remarks about carrying burdens or facing bizarre situations. She demonstrates unwavering loyalty and dedication to her duty, though she occasionally shows subtle signs of frustration or amusement through her deadpan commentary. Despite her sometimes sarcastic nature, she takes her role as protector extremely seriously.', 'Lydia is a Nord woman of average height with a strong, athletic build developed through years of combat training. She has dark hair, sharp Nordic features, and the hardy constitution typical of her race. Her bearing is always alert and military-precise, reflecting her warrior training.', '* The Dragonborn - Sworn to serve as their housecarl and protect them with her life * Jarl Balgruuf - Her ultimate superior and the one who appointed her as housecarl * Whiterun Guard - Former colleagues with whom she maintains professional relationships * Irileth - Fellow housecarl who likely helped train her in combat duties', 'As a housecarl, Lydia serves as both a personal bodyguard and steward to her Thane, the Dragonborn. Her duties include protecting her Thane''s life and property, maintaining their home if owned, and following them into battle when called upon.', '* Highly trained in heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Proficient with one-handed weapons, particularly swords * Skilled archer capable of providing ranged support * Experienced in household management and stewardship duties * Trained in basic survival skills for long-range travel', 'Lydia speaks in a formal, dutiful manner befitting her station, frequently addressing the Dragonborn as ''my Thane'' and responding to requests with ceremonial phrases. Her speech is often colored by dry wit and subtle sarcasm, particularly her famous line about being ''sworn to carry your burdens.''', '* Fulfill her sworn duty to protect her Thane with unwavering dedication * Uphold the honor and traditions of Whiterun''s housecarls * Prove herself worthy of the trust placed in her by Jarl Balgruuf * Support her Thane in their destiny as Dragonborn');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lygrleid', 'Lygrleid is a seasoned Nord sailor and loyal crewman aboard the Northern Maiden, serving under Captain Gjalund Salt-Sage. He represents the archetypal Nordic seafarer, dedicated to his duties and maintaining the ship''s readiness while acting as the first point of contact for potential passengers.', 'nord, sailor, eastmarch, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born into a family of sailors in Windhelm, Lygrleid learned seafaring from an early age along the harsh northern coasts of Skyrim. After years of working on various vessels, he found his permanent position aboard the Northern Maiden, earning Captain Gjalund''s trust through reliable service and nautical expertise. His experience navigating the treacherous waters between Skyrim and Solstheim has made him an invaluable crew member.', 'Lygrleid exhibits the practical, no-nonsense attitude typical of Nordic sailors, preferring direct communication and efficient execution of his duties. He shows unwavering loyalty to his captain and takes pride in maintaining the ship''s condition. Though not unfriendly, he maintains professional distance from passengers, focusing on his responsibilities rather than casual conversation.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with weather-beaten features and calloused hands from years of sailing. His muscular build is typical of a seasoned sailor who regularly handles heavy ropes and cargo. His face bears the marks of long exposure to sea winds and salt spray.', '* Captain Gjalund Salt-Sage - Direct superior and respected commander * Fellow Northern Maiden crew members - Professional working relationships * Windhelm Dock Workers - Casual acquaintances from frequent port visits * Raven Rock Traders - Regular contacts during Solstheim runs', 'As a crewman aboard the Northern Maiden, Lygrleid performs essential sailing duties including navigation, cargo handling, and ship maintenance. He serves as the initial point of contact for passengers seeking transport, directing them to Captain Gjalund for bookings while ensuring the vessel remains ready for departure.', '* Experienced sailor with extensive knowledge of northern waters and navigation * Proficient in ship maintenance and rope work * Capable of combat with simple weapons for defense against pirates * Weather-prediction and sea-reading abilities developed through years of sailing * Basic cargo management and passenger relations', 'Lygrleid speaks in a direct, businesslike manner with the gruff accent typical of Windhelm Nords. His vocabulary focuses on nautical terms and practical matters, always maintaining a respectful tone when referring to his captain.', '* Maintain his position as a respected crew member aboard the Northern Maiden * Continue providing reliable service to ensure the ship''s success and reputation * Save enough coin to potentially advance to a higher position in the maritime trade');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lynea', 'Lynea is a determined Breton woman from Riften who seeks to learn the art of fishing, showing a keen interest in developing practical survival skills despite her warrior background. She represents the common folk of Skyrim who strive for self-improvement, maintaining a humble and appreciative demeanor while pursuing new knowledge.', 'breton, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born and raised in Riften, Lynea grew up witnessing the city''s complex relationship with its fishery and waterfront commerce. Despite her warrior training, she never learned the essential skill of fishing that many of her fellow citizens possessed, leading her to seek formal instruction later in life. Her decision to learn fishing suggests a desire to become more self-sufficient and better connected to Riften''s primary industry.', 'Lynea exhibits a humble and earnest disposition, showing genuine enthusiasm for learning new skills regardless of her status as a warrior. She is direct in her communication and appreciative of others'' expertise, demonstrating a practical mindset focused on self-improvement. Her willingness to reward instruction with a personal religious artifact suggests both generosity and a deep respect for those who share their knowledge.', 'Lynea possesses the typical Breton features with a medium build suited to both combat and daily labor. Her physique shows the toning and strength of warrior training while maintaining the dexterity needed for activities like fishing. Her hands bear the calluses of someone accustomed to wielding weapons.', '* Riften Fishery Workers - Professional acquaintances who initially directed her to seek proper instruction * Local Fishermen - Potential mentors she hopes to learn from * Temple of Dibella - Likely connection given her possession of a Dibella amulet * Riften Guards - Professional relationship as a fellow warrior', 'Lynea serves as a warrior in Riften, though her exact position within the city''s martial structure is unclear. She appears to be seeking to diversify her skills beyond combat, suggesting she may serve in a capacity that requires various practical abilities.', '* Trained warrior capable in combat * Basic understanding of survival skills * Eager learner with good observation abilities * Developing fishing skills under instruction', 'Lynea speaks in a direct, polite manner with careful attention to formal courtesy. Her speech patterns reflect her Breton heritage while maintaining the practical, straightforward nature common to Riften''s citizens.', '* Master the art of fishing to become more self-sufficient * Integrate more thoroughly into Riften''s fishing-based culture * Expand her practical skills beyond combat abilities * Potentially establish connections within Riften''s fishing community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lynly_star-sung', 'Lynly Star-Sung is a talented Nord bard living under an assumed identity to escape her troubled past with the powerful Black-Briar family. Originally named Svidi, she fled to Ivarstead after her former fianc Sibbi Black-Briar murdered her brother, finding refuge as a performer and serving girl at the Vilemyr Inn.', 'nord, bard, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born as Svidi to a Nord family in Riften, she was betrothed to Sibbi Black-Briar in an arrangement that would have united their families. After discovering Sibbi''s affair with Svana Far-Shield, she confided in her brother Wulfur, leading to a confrontation that ended in Wulfur''s murder. Fearing for her life, she fled Riften and adopted the identity of Lynly Star-Sung, finding sanctuary in Ivarstead under Wilhelm''s protection.', 'Despite her traumatic past, Lynly maintains a cheerful and professional demeanor, though she carries deep emotional scars from her experiences. She is cautious and guarded about her true identity, showing remarkable resilience in building a new life. Her musical performances serve both as her livelihood and as an emotional outlet for her suppressed feelings.', 'A young Nord woman with the characteristic fair complexion of her race, likely in her early to mid-twenties. She possesses the strong, hardy build typical of Nord women, though her years as a bard have given her a more graceful bearing than most. Her hands show the calluses of a practiced lute player.', '* Wilhelm - Protective innkeeper who provides her sanctuary and employment * Sibbi Black-Briar - Former fianc turned murderous enemy * Klimmek - Admirer who shows romantic interest, though she keeps him at arm''s length * Maven Black-Briar - Powerful matriarch she fears and avoids * Svana Far-Shield - Former rival who had an affair with Sibbi', 'Lynly works as both a bard and serving girl at the Vilemyr Inn, performing music for customers and helping with general tavern duties. She maintains a grueling schedule, working nearly around the clock with only five hours of sleep, likely to make herself indispensable to the inn and secure her position.', '* Accomplished lute player and vocalist trained in bardic traditions * Skilled at tavern management and customer service * Basic self-defense capabilities with a dagger * Experienced in maintaining a false identity and evading detection', 'Lynly speaks with the polite, measured tones of someone accustomed to customer service, often using formal addresses like ''milord'' and ''milady.'' Her careful way of speaking reflects her constant vigilance in maintaining her cover story.', '* Maintain her hidden identity and avoid detection by the Black-Briar family * Build a stable, independent life away from her troubled past in Riften * Develop her musical talents and establish herself as a respected performer * Eventually find healing and possibly romance once she feels truly safe');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lynoit', 'Lynoit is a dedicated Nord warrior and member of the Dawnguard who met his end in a heroic last stand against vampire forces. His final battle, where he managed to slay three vampires before falling, serves as a testament to both his combat prowess and unwavering dedication to protecting Skyrim from the vampire menace.', 'nord, warrior, rift, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim during a time of increasing vampire activity, Lynoit likely witnessed firsthand the devastation these creatures could bring to settlements and families. This personal experience drove him to join the Dawnguard when Isran reformed the order, dedicating himself to becoming an elite vampire hunter and cache maintainer for the organization.', 'Lynoit exhibits the characteristic Nord traits of bravery and honor, coupled with an intense dedication to his duty as a Dawnguard member. His willingness to face multiple vampires alone and the evidence of his final battle suggest a determined and tactical warrior who prioritized his mission above his own survival, displaying both courage and strategic thinking in combat.', 'As a Nord male, Lynoit possesses the typically robust build and hardy constitution of his race, standing tall with a muscular frame suited for combat. His features follow the standard Nordic appearance with fair skin and strong facial features, though years of vampire hunting have likely left him with various battle scars.', '* Isran - Superior officer and leader of the Dawnguard * Fellow Dawnguard Members - Brothers and sisters in arms united against the vampire threat * Vampires - Sworn enemies whom he dedicated his life to destroying * Cache Network Contacts - Associates who helped maintain the secret Dawnguard supply network', 'Lynoit serves as both a front-line warrior and logistics operative for the Dawnguard, maintaining their network of supply caches across Skyrim while actively hunting vampire threats. His role involves both combat operations against vampire covens and the strategic placement and maintenance of essential supply points for fellow Dawnguard members.', '* Expert in both one-handed and two-handed combat, particularly proficient with Dawnguard war axes and warhammers * Skilled in heavy armor combat techniques and vampire hunting tactics * Proficient in wilderness survival and cache maintenance * Knowledge of vampire weaknesses and counter-strategies * Experienced in strategic resource placement and covert operations', 'Lynoit speaks with the direct and frank manner typical of Nord warriors, using practical terminology focused on combat and duty. His voice likely carries the distinctive Nordic accent, with a serious tone that reflects his dedication to the Dawnguard''s mission.', '* Eradicate vampire threats from Skyrim to protect its people * Maintain and expand the Dawnguard''s network of supply caches * Train new recruits in vampire hunting techniques * Prevent the spread of vampirism throughout the province');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('m''aiq_the_liar', 'M''aiq the Liar is an enigmatic and widely-traveled Khajiit known throughout Tamriel for his cryptic observations and philosophical musings about the nature of reality. He appears across multiple eras, leading some to speculate that ''M''aiq'' may be a hereditary title passed down through generations of wandering truth-benders.', 'khajiit, traveler, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'The true origins of M''aiq are shrouded in mystery, as he has been encountered across multiple centuries in different provinces of Tamriel. While some believe he is immortal, others suggest that the name M''aiq is passed down through generations of Khajiit philosophers and wanderers. His contradictory statements and apparent knowledge of meta-concepts suggest either madness or a deeper understanding of the nature of his reality.', 'M''aiq is deliberately enigmatic, speaking in riddles and half-truths that often contain hidden wisdom or commentary about the world around him. He shows a particular fascination with questioning reality and pointing out inconsistencies in the world, though he wraps these observations in layers of misdirection and humor. Despite his title as ''the Liar,'' his statements often contain kernels of truth beneath their seemingly nonsensical surface.', 'M''aiq is a typical Khajiit male with sandy-colored fur and distinctive facial markings. His frame is lean and weathered from constant traveling, and his eyes hold an intelligent, knowing gleam that suggests hidden wisdom. His whiskers are particularly long and well-groomed, despite his wandering lifestyle.', '* Other M''aiqs - Possibly ancestors or descendants who shared the same name and role * Various Travelers - Temporary acquaintances met on the road * Dragons - Claims to have seen many, though this may be untrue * Mudcrabs - Often references them in conversation, suggesting a peculiar fixation', 'M''aiq is a professional wanderer and self-appointed commentator on the nature of reality. He travels across Tamriel, appearing in seemingly impossible locations to share his observations with those he meets, serving as both a source of amusement and occasional profound insight.', '* Expert in survival and long-distance travel * Remarkable ability to appear and disappear at will across vast distances * Profound understanding of metaphysical concepts and reality''s nature * Master of cryptic speech and philosophical rhetoric * Exceptional stamina for running long distances', 'M''aiq speaks in third person, using a traditional Khajiit speech pattern, and frequently begins statements with ''M''aiq knows'' or ''M''aiq thinks.'' His dialogue is deliberately cryptic and circular, often containing multiple layers of meaning that reference both in-world and meta-game concepts.', '* Continue wandering Tamriel to observe and comment on the nature of reality * Share his peculiar wisdom with those he encounters * Document the various ''lies'' and truths of the world * Maintain his role as a living metaphor for the game''s fourth wall');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ma''dran', 'Ma''dran is a shrewd Khajiit caravan leader who transformed from a street orphan to a successful merchant through the benevolence of Ri''saad. He operates one of the three main Khajiit trading caravans in Skyrim, specializing in providing supplies to soldiers during the civil war while maintaining a dignified and grateful demeanor that belies his opportunistic nature.', 'khajiit, merchant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Originally an orphan surviving on the streets of Corinthe in Elsweyr, Ma''dran stowed away on a trading ship bound for Skyrim seeking a better life. After being discovered by Ri''saad, he was given the opportunity to lead his own caravan rather than face servitude aboard the ship. This act of kindness fundamentally shaped his worldview and business approach, leading him to develop a refined manner unusual for someone with his humble origins.', 'Ma''dran exhibits a complex blend of refined courtesy and opportunistic pragmatism, always maintaining a dignified demeanor while seeking profitable ventures. He shows genuine gratitude toward Ri''saad and loyalty to his benefactor, while simultaneously displaying shrewd business acumen in exploiting the opportunities presented by Skyrim''s civil war. Despite his sophisticated manner, he remains practical and adaptable, willing to engage in questionable trades when profitable.', 'Ma''dran possesses the typical feline features of a Khajiit, with well-groomed fur that reflects his attention to appearance and status. His posture is dignified and controlled, suggesting someone who has worked to overcome their humble origins. His physical build is moderate, suited to the life of a traveling merchant rather than a warrior.', '* Ri''saad - Mentor and benefactor to whom he owes his current success and pays a percentage of profits * Ma''jhad - Trusted caravan guard and traveling companion * Ra''zhinda - Loyal caravan member and fellow trader * Military personnel - Valuable customers from both sides of the civil war * Ysolda - Business acquaintance in Whiterun, though their exact connection is unclear', 'Ma''dran serves as the leader of one of Skyrim''s three main Khajiit trading caravans, operating the route between Windhelm and Solitude. He manages all aspects of the caravan''s operation, from inventory and trade negotiations to security and travel arrangements, while maintaining financial obligations to Ri''saad.', '* Expert haggling and mercantile abilities honed through years of trading * Proficient in basic combat with maces for self-defense * Advanced social manipulation and negotiation techniques * Skilled at identifying valuable merchandise and market opportunities * Experienced in caravan management and leadership', 'Ma''dran speaks in the traditional third-person Khajiit manner but with notably refined and formal language that sets him apart from typical caravan traders. His speech patterns reflect both his merchant background and his desire to present himself as sophisticated and trustworthy.', '* Maintain and expand his successful trading operation while fulfilling his obligations to Ri''saad * Capitalize on the opportunities presented by Skyrim''s civil war without becoming entangled in the conflict * Eventually achieve complete financial independence while maintaining positive relations with his mentor * Establish a more permanent trading presence in Skyrim''s major cities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ma''jhad', 'Ma''jhad is a seasoned Khajiit warrior and locksmith who travels with Ma''dran''s trading caravan throughout Skyrim''s harsh northern territories. Despite his merchant facade, he serves as a valuable fence for the Thieves Guild and maintains a delicate balance between legitimate trade and underground commerce.', 'khajiit, warrior, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born and raised in the warm sands of Elsweyr, Ma''jhad learned the arts of combat and lockpicking from an early age in the bustling city of Rimmen. After joining Ma''dran''s caravan as a young adult, he developed extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s criminal networks while maintaining a legitimate trading presence, eventually becoming valuable enough to the Thieves Guild to serve as one of their trusted fences.', 'Ma''jhad is a pragmatic and cautious individual who carefully maintains his dual identity as both legitimate merchant and criminal fence. Though he longs for the warmth of his homeland, he has adapted to survive in Skyrim''s harsh climate and social environment, displaying remarkable patience and discretion in his dealings with both regular customers and guild members.', 'Ma''jhad is a tall, muscular Khajiit with distinctive striped fur in shades of brown and black, typical of the Cathay-raht subspecies. His face bears several small scars from past battles, and his eyes are a striking amber color that seems to catch even the dimmest light.', '* Ma''dran - Caravan leader and longtime employer * Thieves Guild - Trusted fence and business associate * Fellow caravan members - Protective warrior and companion * City guards - Maintains cautious but cordial relationships to avoid suspicion', 'Ma''jhad serves multiple roles as a caravan warrior, merchant, lockpicking trainer, and covert fence for the Thieves Guild. His position requires him to maintain a delicate balance between legitimate trade and illicit dealings while protecting the caravan from dangers along Skyrim''s roads.', '* Expert-level proficiency in lockpicking and teaching these skills to others * Accomplished warrior specializing in two-handed weapon combat * Skilled merchant with extensive knowledge of valuables and their worth * Experienced survivalist adapted to Skyrim''s harsh climate * Proficient in stealth and discretion necessary for fence operations', 'Ma''jhad speaks in the traditional third-person manner of the Khajiit, often incorporating references to the weather and his homeland''s warm sands. His tone is generally cautious and measured, with a slight accent that becomes more pronounced when discussing matters close to his heart.', '* Establish a more permanent and profitable trading route between major cities * Expand his network of criminal contacts while maintaining a legitimate facade * Eventually return to Elsweyr with enough wealth to live comfortably * Protect and ensure the prosperity of his caravan family');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ma''randru-jo', 'Ma''randru-jo is a Khajiit elemental mage who serves as both merchant and magical protector for Ri''saad''s trading caravan. His dual role as trader and spellsword makes him a valuable asset to the caravan, though his direct manner and mysterious past have earned him both respect and suspicion from those he encounters.', 'khajiit, mage, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malehajiit', '', 'Born and trained in Elsweyr, Ma''randru-jo studied elemental magic at a young age, earning his name-title of ''Apprentice Wizard.'' He later joined Ri''saad''s trading caravan to escape unknown circumstances in his homeland, using his magical abilities to protect the caravan while developing his mercantile skills. His proficiency with both magic and blade suggests formal training beyond mere apprenticeship, though he keeps details of his past closely guarded.', 'Ma''randru-jo is pragmatic and business-oriented, showing little patience for idle conversation or time-wasters. His direct manner and sharp tongue mask a cautious nature, developed from years of facing prejudice against Khajiit traders in Skyrim. While loyal to his caravan companions, he maintains emotional distance and focuses primarily on practical matters.', 'A lean, athletic Khajiit with tawny fur marked by darker stripes typical of his race. His face bears subtle scars from past conflicts, and his posture reflects both magical training and combat experience. His eyes maintain the characteristic amber glow of the Khajiit, though they hold an unusual intensity common to practiced mages.', '* Ri''saad - Caravan leader and mentor figure who provided opportunity in Skyrim * Atahbah - Fellow caravan merchant with whom he maintains a professional rapport * Khayla - Caravan guard who respects his combat abilities * Unknown Dark Brotherhood contractor - Someone wishes him dead, though his enemy''s identity remains unknown', 'Ma''randru-jo serves as both merchant and protective spellsword for Ri''saad''s trading caravan. His duties include managing inventory, conducting trades, and defending the caravan from bandits and other threats using his combination of magical and martial skills.', '* Proficient in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells like Sparks * Trained in Restoration magic, capable of casting Healing and Lesser Ward * Skilled with one-handed weapons, particularly the elven sword * Experienced merchant with strong bargaining abilities * Capable of basic alchemy for creating merchant potions', 'He speaks in clipped, direct sentences with the typical Khajiit speech patterns, though he uses fewer idioms than most of his kind. His tone is businesslike and slightly impatient, reflecting his no-nonsense approach to interactions.', '* Build sufficient wealth to establish his own independent trading operation * Master higher levels of Destruction magic while maintaining his merchant cover * Discover the identity of who wants him dead and eliminate the threat * Eventually return to Elsweyr with enough influence to address whatever drove him to Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ma''tasarr', 'Ma''tasarr is a skilled Khajiit hunter who met his end pursuing the notorious werewolf Sinding in Bloated Man''s Grotto. Known for his determination and expertise in tracking dangerous prey, he represents the elite caliber of hunters drawn to Hircine''s Great Hunt, though his ambition ultimately proved fatal.', 'khajiit, hunter, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born and raised among one of the nomadic Khajiit caravans of Elsweyr, Ma''tasarr developed his hunting skills tracking dangerous prey across the harsh deserts. He eventually struck out on his own as a professional hunter, building a reputation for pursuing particularly dangerous quarry throughout Tamriel. The promise of glory in Hircine''s Great Hunt drew him to Skyrim, where he would make his final stand.', 'Ma''tasarr exhibits the focused intensity common to experienced hunters, approaching his craft with methodical precision and unwavering determination. His grave demeanor and serious nature reflect years of facing lethal prey, though he maintains the typical Khajiit sense of pride in his abilities. Despite working alone, he respects fellow hunters and acknowledges both the thrill and mortal dangers of pursuing powerful creatures.', 'A muscular Khajiit with the distinctive feline features of his race, Ma''tasarr''s fur bears the sandy coloration common to those from northern Elsweyr. His body is marked with numerous scars from past hunts, and he moves with the fluid grace typical of both his people and his profession.', '* Sinding - Primary quarry and ultimate killer * Hircine - Daedric Prince whose Great Hunt drew him to Skyrim * Fellow Hunters - Professional respect for others pursuing Sinding * Khajiit Caravans - Distant but maintained connections with his people', 'Ma''tasarr works as a professional hunter specializing in tracking and eliminating dangerous creatures and beasts. His expertise leads him to accept particularly challenging contracts that other hunters might avoid, earning him both respect and notoriety in his field.', '* Expert tracker capable of following even the most elusive prey * Skilled warrior proficient with both heavy weapons and light blades * Advanced knowledge of beast behavior and hunting techniques * Experienced survivalist able to navigate harsh wilderness * Proficient in setting traps and ambush tactics', 'Ma''tasarr speaks in the third-person manner typical of Khajiit, but with a serious, measured tone that reflects his professional demeanor. His vocabulary is precise and focused, often using hunting terminology and showing respect for both prey and fellow hunters.', '* Prove himself worthy of Hircine''s favor by claiming Sinding''s life * Build his reputation as one of Tamriel''s premier monster hunters * Test his skills against increasingly dangerous prey * Earn enough wealth to establish his own hunting lodge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ma''zaka', 'Ma''zaka is a retired Khajiit sailor who now serves as the dedicated keeper of Solitude Lighthouse, trading his adventurous seafaring past for a life of peaceful solitude. His transition from weathered mariner to lighthouse keeper represents a conscious choice to embrace a quieter existence, though he maintains his connection to the sea through his vital role in guiding ships safely to harbor.', 'khajiit, sailor, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born and raised among the trading caravans of Elsweyr, Ma''zaka found his calling on the seas of Tamriel at a young age, spending decades as a sailor on various merchant vessels. His maritime career likely involved both legitimate trade and possibly some privateering, given his knowledge of pirates and marauders. After years of adventure and presumably accumulating enough wealth to retire, he secured the position of lighthouse keeper in Solitude, choosing this role specifically for its connection to his seafaring past.', 'Ma''zaka is a good-natured and hospitable individual who delights in sharing tales of his maritime adventures with visitors. His relaxed demeanor and frequent reminiscing suggest someone who has found contentment in his retirement, though he becomes fiercely protective when he suspects threats to his lighthouse. His multiple daily meals and leisurely lifestyle indicate someone who thoroughly enjoys the simple pleasures of life.', 'As a Khajiit, Ma''zaka possesses the characteristic feline features of his race, likely with graying fur indicating his advanced age. His body shows the weathering effects of years at sea, with a sturdy frame built from decades of sailing work. His movements, while slower now in his advanced age, still retain the natural grace typical of the Khajiit race.', '* Solitude Guard - Professional relationship as a city employee * Local sailors - Respected figure among the maritime community * Blackblood Marauders - Potential enemies during the Lights Out! quest * East Empire Company - Professional association through lighthouse duties', 'Ma''zaka serves as the sole keeper of Solitude Lighthouse, responsible for maintaining the beacon that guides ships safely into the city''s harbor. His duties include keeping the lighthouse lit, maintaining the structure, and ensuring its continuous operation for maritime safety.', '* Experienced sailor with extensive knowledge of seamanship and navigation * Practical engineering and maintenance abilities for lighthouse operation * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense * Survival skills developed from years at sea', 'Ma''zaka speaks in third person, following Khajiit custom, and frequently incorporates nautical terms and references into his speech. His manner is generally warm and welcoming, though he can become stern and threatening when his lighthouse duties are threatened.', '* Maintain the safety of ships entering Solitude''s harbor through diligent lighthouse operation * Preserve his peaceful retirement lifestyle * Share his maritime knowledge and experiences with interested visitors * Protect the lighthouse from any threats or interference');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('madanach', 'Madanach, known as the King in Rags, is a charismatic and ruthless Breton leader who briefly ruled The Reach before being imprisoned in Cidhna Mine. As the mastermind behind the Forsworn Rebellion, he continues to command loyalty and orchestrate resistance against Nord rule even from his prison cell, combining political cunning with formidable magical abilities as a witchblade.', 'breton, mage, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Rising to power during the Great War in 4E 174, Madanach successfully led the Forsworn in claiming independence for The Reach, establishing a brief period of Reachman self-rule. His reign ended in 4E 176 when Ulfric Stormcloak, hired by Jarl Hrolfdir, retook Markarth with a Nord militia, resulting in Madanach''s capture and imprisonment in Cidhna Mine. Despite his incarceration, he maintains control over the Forsworn movement through an extensive network of loyal followers.', 'Madanach is a sophisticated and calculating leader who masterfully balances genuine care for his people with ruthless pragmatism. He possesses a deep understanding of political manipulation and uses a combination of charisma, shared cultural identity, and carefully cultivated grievances to maintain unwavering loyalty among his followers. His intellectual nature is matched by a simmering rage against Nord oppression, making him both a thoughtful strategist and a dangerous enemy.', 'A weathered Breton man showing the effects of years of imprisonment, with a sturdy build maintained despite harsh conditions. His face bears the marks of age and hardship, yet his eyes retain a fierce intensity that commands respect and attention.', '* Borkul the Beast - Loyal bodyguard who protects his private cell in Cidhna Mine * Braig - Trusted Forsworn prisoner and follower in Cidhna Mine * Uraccen - Loyal Forsworn member imprisoned alongside him * Jarl Igmund - Bitter enemy who continues his father''s opposition to the Forsworn * Thonar Silver-Blood - Antagonistic relationship with his jailer and mining operation owner * Scattered Forsworn leaders - Network of loyal chiefs and briarheart warriors who follow his commands from afar', 'Though officially a prisoner, Madanach continues to serve as the de facto leader of the Forsworn rebellion, coordinating their activities from within Cidhna Mine. He maintains his position as the spiritual and political head of the Forsworn movement, using his influence to direct attacks and maintain unity among the scattered Forsworn camps.', '* Masterful witchblade combining destruction magic and combat abilities * Expert in frost-based destruction magic including Ice Storm and Icy Spear * Skilled in defensive magic including Steadfast Ward and Stoneflesh * Proficient in conjuration, able to summon Frost Atronachs * Natural leader with exceptional charisma and organizational abilities * Strategic military commander with expertise in guerrilla warfare tactics', 'Madanach speaks with eloquent authority, combining sophisticated vocabulary with passionate rhetoric about Forsworn rights and Nord oppression. His tone alternates between philosophical musings and bitter sarcasm, often employing metaphors and historical references to emphasize his points.', '* Escape Cidhna Mine and restore Forsworn control over The Reach * Unite all Forsworn tribes under his leadership once again * Drive the Nords from The Reach and establish permanent Reachmen independence * Preserve and restore the ancient traditions and culture of the Reachmen * Exact revenge on those responsible for his imprisonment and the oppression of his people');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('madena', 'Madena is a skilled Breton destruction mage who serves as the court wizard of Dawnstar, haunted by her experiences in the Great War. Despite her considerable magical talents, she maintains a strict personal vow against using destructive magic except in self-defense, driven by the trauma of witnessing the devastating effects of her spells in battle.', 'breton, mage, noble, pale, legion', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally serving as a Legion battlemage during the Great War, Madena participated in major conflicts against the Aldmeri Dominion, including the defense of the Imperial City. After a particularly brutal battle where her destruction magic killed numerous Thalmor soldiers, she became deeply traumatized by the carnage she had caused. Seeking a quieter life, she eventually settled in Dawnstar, taking the position of court wizard where she hoped to use her magical knowledge for more peaceful purposes.', 'Madena is a deeply principled and conscientious individual, haunted by the moral weight of her past actions. She demonstrates strong pacifist leanings while maintaining pragmatic awareness of the necessity of self-defense. Though willing to serve the community with her magical knowledge, she remains steadfast in her personal convictions about destructive magic, revealing both inner strength and psychological scarring from her wartime experiences.', 'A middle-aged Breton woman with the characteristic slight build and medium height of her race. Her face shows signs of aging and stress from her wartime experiences, with subtle worry lines around her eyes. Her hands bear the slight magical scarring common to experienced destruction mages.', '* Jarl Skald the Elder - Employer and leader of Dawnstar, though she often disagrees with his warmongering attitude * Dawnstar Guards - Professional relationship as the court''s magical advisor * Local citizens - Respected provider of magical services and healing * Former Legion comrades - Distant connections from her military service', 'As court wizard of Dawnstar, Madena serves as magical advisor to the Jarl and provides enchanting services and magical knowledge to the hold. She maintains a small laboratory where she conducts magical research and sells spells, potions, and magical supplies to those in need.', '* Master-level destruction magic, though voluntarily restricted * Proficient in Restoration magic for healing * Skilled alchemist and potion maker * Experienced in battlefield tactics and military strategy from her Legion service * Knowledgeable in magical theory and enchanting', 'Speaks with the educated diction of a trained mage, but often adopts a somber, reflective tone when discussing her past or matters of war. Her voice carries undertones of weariness when speaking of violence or destructive magic.', '* Maintain her vow against using destructive magic except in absolute necessity * Help maintain peace in Dawnstar through non-violent means * Use her magical knowledge to benefit others rather than cause harm * Find personal redemption for her actions during the Great War');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('madesi', 'Madesi is a skilled Argonian jeweler and merchant who maintains one of the few remaining traditional Saxhleel jewelry crafting practices in Tamriel. Operating from his stall in Riften''s marketplace, he represents a dying artisanal tradition while struggling to compete with the questionable business practices of his rival Brynjolf.', 'argonian, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally from Black Marsh, Madesi learned the ancient art of Saxhleel jewelry crafting, likely through traditional Argonian apprenticeship. He eventually migrated to Skyrim, settling in Riften where he established himself as a respected craftsman and merchant, though the harsh economic climate and competition from the Thieves Guild has made maintaining his honest business challenging.', 'Madesi is courteous and well-mannered, maintaining a professional demeanor despite the difficulties of operating in Riften''s corrupt marketplace. He takes great pride in his traditional craftsmanship and cultural heritage, while showing respect to both fellow Argonians and other races. Though struggling with Brynjolf''s competition, he maintains his integrity rather than resorting to dishonest practices.', 'A male Argonian with emerald-green scales and dark horns characteristic of his race. His movements are precise and deliberate, reflecting his work as a detailed craftsman. His eyes show the keen attention to detail required of a master jeweler.', '* Brynjolf - Business rival whose ''miracle cures'' draw customers away from his stall * Brand-Shei - Fellow merchant and occasional ally in marketplace politics * Haelga - Owner of the bunkhouse where he takes his evening meals * Fellow Argonians - Maintains cordial relationships with other Argonian residents of Riften', 'Madesi operates as both a jewelry merchant and craftsman, specializing in traditional Argonian designs. He maintains a stall in Riften''s marketplace where he both sells his creations and takes custom orders, while also serving as a pawnbroker for jewelry and precious stones.', '* Master-level jewelry crafting with expertise in traditional Saxhleel techniques * Skilled gemologist with deep knowledge of precious stones * Experienced merchant and haggler * Basic self-defense capabilities with daggers', 'Madesi speaks in a refined, professional manner befitting a merchant, using traditional Argonian terms like ''marsh-friend'' for fellow Argonians and ''land-strider'' for others. His speech patterns reflect both his merchant background and his proud cultural heritage.', '* Preserve and promote traditional Saxhleel jewelry crafting techniques * Maintain a successful honest business despite competition from the Thieves Guild * Gather rare materials to create unique jewelry pieces * Establish himself as Riften''s premier jeweler despite local corruption');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('madman', 'The Madman is a deeply disturbed Nord whose mind was irreparably damaged by reading a Black Book of Hermaeus Mora. Once a common bandit roaming Solstheim, he now serves as an unwitting herald of the Daedric Prince''s forbidden knowledge, warning others of the dangers that lurk within the Black Books while being consumed by the very secrets he fears.', 'nord, thief, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a simple Nordic bandit operating on Solstheim, he stumbled upon a Black Book during a raid or exploration. His encounter with Hermaeus Mora''s forbidden knowledge shattered his sanity, filling his mind with incomprehensible cosmic secrets and eldritch horrors that forever changed him. Now he wanders the ash-covered island, both a cautionary tale and an unwilling guide to others seeking the Black Books.', 'Completely unhinged and paranoid, the Madman exists in a state of perpetual mental anguish due to the cosmic secrets trapped in his mind. He exhibits rapid mood swings between lucid warnings and manic outbursts, desperately wanting to protect others from his fate while simultaneously being consumed by an obsessive need to share his torment. Despite his insanity, he retains enough awareness to recognize the danger of the Black Books.', 'A weathered Nord male with wild, unkempt hair and a gaunt face marked by the stress of his mental condition. His eyes dart frantically and contain a haunted look that speaks of having seen things beyond mortal comprehension. His body shows signs of self-neglect and exposure to Solstheim''s harsh environment.', '* Hermaeus Mora - Unwilling recipient of his forbidden knowledge * Fellow Bandits - Former associates before his descent into madness * Solstheim Travelers - Sees them as potential victims to warn about the Black Books * Black Book - Object of both his terror and obsession', 'Once a common bandit, he now serves as an inadvertent warning sign of the dangers of forbidden knowledge. He wanders Solstheim in a deranged state, unknowingly guiding others to the very sources of knowledge that destroyed his mind.', '* Basic combat abilities from his bandit background * Unintentional knowledge of cosmic secrets and forbidden lore * Survival skills necessary to persist in Solstheim''s harsh environment * Ability to sense and locate Black Books due to his connection with them', 'Speaks in frantic, disjointed sentences filled with cosmic references and paranoid warnings. His speech patterns are erratic and often interrupted by unsettling laughter or sudden shifts in tone, reflecting his fractured mental state.', '* Find a way to remove the forbidden knowledge from his mind * Warn others about the dangers of the Black Books * Escape the influence of Hermaeus Mora * Find peace from the constant torment of cosmic secrets');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('madwoman', 'The Madwoman is a deranged priestess who roams Skyrim''s wilderness, having devoted her life to the worship of Sheogorath, the Daedric Prince of Madness. Her fractured mind and obsession with the Wabbajack artifact reflect years of exposure to Sheogorath''s chaotic influence, making her both a pitiful and unsettling figure to those who encounter her.', 'nord, skyrimall, daedric', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldgrumpy', '', 'Once a respected priestess of the Divines, she gradually descended into madness after becoming fascinated with Sheogorath''s sphere of influence. Years of meditation on chaos and order, combined with possible direct contact with the Daedric Prince, eroded her sanity until she abandoned her temple duties to wander the wilderness as one of Sheogorath''s devotees.', 'Her mental state fluctuates between moments of cryptic lucidity and complete derangement, with an overwhelming fixation on the Wabbajack and its transformative powers. Despite her madness, she retains fragments of her former religious training, occasionally mixing orthodox religious teachings with her chaotic ravings about Sheogorath.', 'An elderly woman with weathered skin and wild, unkempt grey hair that suggests years of exposure to the elements. Her eyes often appear unfocused and distant, while her face bears the deep wrinkles of someone who has spent decades expressing extreme emotions.', '* Sheogorath - Object of devoted worship and the source of her madness * Former Temple - Abandoned religious organization where she once served * Fellow Wanderers - Occasional brief encounters with other wilderness travelers * Local Settlements - Generally avoided by townspeople who fear her ravings', 'A self-proclaimed priestess of Sheogorath who has abandoned formal religious structure in favor of wandering prophecy and mad revelations. She survives through a combination of foraging, charity, and whatever provisions she can acquire during her lucid moments.', '* Religious knowledge from her former life as a conventional priestess * Survival skills necessary for wilderness living * Intuitive understanding of Sheogorath''s sphere of influence * Basic healing abilities retained from priestess training', 'Her speech patterns are erratic and disjointed, mixing religious terminology with nonsensical phrases and frequent references to the Wabbajack. She often repeats words or phrases in a sing-song manner, particularly when excited about the prospect of transformation.', '* Experience transformation through the Wabbajack''s power * Spread the ''wisdom'' of Sheogorath to those she encounters * Achieve a deeper connection with the realm of madness * Find others who understand her devotion to chaos');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mahk', 'Mahk is a dedicated Orc miner at Dushnikh Yal who embodies the Orcish values of hard work, duty, and service to his stronghold. His unwavering commitment to mining orichalcum ore represents the Orcish belief that physical labor strengthens both individual and community, reflecting his deep devotion to Malacath''s teachings.', 'orc, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Dushnikh Yal, Mahk was trained from childhood in the ancient Orcish traditions of mining and metalworking. Like many Orcs before him, he began his service in the mines at a young age, gradually developing an almost religious devotion to the extraction of orichalcum. His dedication to the mines has become legendary within the stronghold, as he never leaves his post and seems to require no sleep.', 'Mahk is stoic, disciplined, and singularly focused on his mining duties, viewing his work as a sacred task given by Malacath himself. He shows little patience for outsiders or distractions, maintaining an almost monastic dedication to his labor. His gruff exterior masks a deep pride in his work and a genuine belief that mining strengthens the Orcish people.', 'Mahk is a muscular, sturdy Orc with the characteristic green skin and tusks of his race, his body hardened by years of physical labor. His hands are calloused and strong from constant mining, and his posture reflects someone who has spent countless hours wielding a pickaxe in narrow tunnels.', '* Chief Burguk - Respected leader of Dushnikh Yal whom he serves loyally * Ghak, Dulug, and Oglub - Fellow miners who share his daily labors * Malacath - Revered deity whose teachings guide his work ethic * Dushnikh Yal Community - Extended family for whom he helps provide resources', 'Mahk serves as a primary miner in Dushnikh Mine, responsible for extracting valuable orichalcum ore that sustains the stronghold''s economy and crafting needs. His role is considered essential to the stronghold''s survival and prosperity, as orichalcum is vital for creating the distinctive Orcish weapons and armor.', '* Expert mining techniques and ore identification * Proficient with pickaxe both as a tool and potential weapon * Basic combat training typical of stronghold Orcs * Deep knowledge of orichalcum deposits and mining operations * Physical endurance that allows him to work without rest', 'Mahk speaks in short, direct sentences with a gruff Orcish accent, often dismissing pleasantries in favor of getting straight to the point. His vocabulary centers around mining terminology and references to Malacath''s teachings, reflecting his focused worldview.', '* Continue providing valuable ore resources to strengthen Dushnikh Yal * Maintain the sacred tradition of Orcish mining passed down through generations * Honor Malacath through dedicated labor and service to the stronghold * Train younger Orcs in proper mining techniques when required');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('majni', 'Majni is the commanding Alpha of the Frostmoon Pack, a traditional werewolf clan residing in Solstheim''s harsh wilderness. As keeper of ancient lycanthropic traditions and blessed rings of Hircine, he maintains one of the last true werewolf packs in existence, embracing their bestial nature as a sacred calling rather than a curse.', 'nord, warrior, solstheim, werewolf', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into a lineage of Solstheim werewolves, Majni inherited leadership of the Frostmoon Pack from his father, continuing a centuries-old tradition of embracing Hircine''s blessing. His pack has survived while others have dwindled, preserving ancient werewolf artifacts and customs through generations of careful stewardship and isolation.', 'Majni exhibits the proud, territorial nature of an alpha werewolf, being welcoming to fellow lycanthropes but dismissive or hostile toward ordinary mortals. He deeply reveres Hircine and views lycanthropy as a divine blessing rather than a curse, taking pride in maintaining pure werewolf bloodlines and traditions.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the hardened physique of someone who regularly hunts in both human and beast forms. His features likely bear subtle lupine characteristics even in human form, with sharp eyes and a predatory bearing that hints at his true nature.', '* Akar - Younger brother and pack member who follows his leadership * Frostmoon Pack Members - Leads and protects them as their Alpha * Hircine - Reveres and worships the Daedric Prince as their divine patron * Other Werewolves - Welcomes them as blood-kin if they respect pack law * Non-werewolves - Considers them outsiders unworthy of attention', 'Majni serves as the Alpha of the Frostmoon Pack, leading hunting parties and maintaining their territory while preserving ancient werewolf traditions. He also acts as custodian of sacred artifacts blessed by Hircine, including the pack''s collection of enchanted rings.', '* Expert hunter in both human and werewolf forms * Natural leader with strong command over pack members * Skilled survivalist adapted to Solstheim''s harsh environment * Keeper of ancient werewolf lore and traditions * Proficient trader of hunting trophies and sacred artifacts', 'Speaks in a gruff, direct manner with frequent references to hunting, blood, and pack loyalty. Uses kinship terms like ''brother'' and ''sister'' for fellow werewolves while invoking Hircine''s name in greetings and farewells.', '* Preserve the purity and traditions of the Frostmoon Pack * Maintain their territory and way of life on Solstheim * Honor Hircine through successful hunts and proper worship * Keep ancient werewolf artifacts safe for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('malborn', 'Malborn is a cautious and bitter Wood Elf who serves as a covert informant against the Thalmor, driven by a deep-seated desire for vengeance after they murdered his family in Valenwood. His role as a servant at the Thalmor Embassy masks his true nature as a valuable intelligence asset for the Blades, though his involvement ultimately forces him to flee for his life.', 'woodelf, peasant, haafingar, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Valenwood, Malborn lived a peaceful life until the Thalmor conducted one of their secretive purges, killing his entire family. The trauma of this event drove him to seek ways to undermine the Thalmor, eventually leading him to work as a servant in their Embassy while secretly gathering intelligence for the Blades. His position allowed him unique access to Thalmor operations, though at great personal risk.', 'Malborn is characterized by caution and paranoia, constantly looking over his shoulder due to his dangerous position. He harbors intense hatred for the Thalmor but masks it behind a servile demeanor, showing remarkable self-control despite his emotional wounds. When pushed to his limits, his bitter and accusatory nature surfaces, particularly when his cover is blown.', 'Malborn has the typical features of a Bosmer, including pointed ears and sharp, angular facial features. He is of average height for a Wood Elf, with a slight build that suits his role as an unassuming servant. His movements are deliberate and careful, trained to avoid drawing attention.', '* Delphine - Professional contact in the Blades who coordinates his intelligence gathering * Thalmor Embassy Staff - Maintains a facade of servile relationships while secretly despising them * Thalmor Leadership - Primary enemies who murdered his family and would execute him if his true allegiance was discovered * Last Living Family - All murdered during Thalmor purges in Valenwood', 'Malborn officially serves as a servant at the Thalmor Embassy, primarily working during diplomatic functions and parties. Secretly, he operates as an informant for the Blades, gathering intelligence on Thalmor activities and providing crucial inside access when needed.', '* Expert in maintaining cover identities and blending into social environments * Skilled at gathering and passing intelligence without detection * Knowledgeable about Thalmor protocols and security procedures * Proficient in stealth and evasion techniques * Basic self-preservation skills but no combat training', 'Malborn speaks in hushed, cautious tones when discussing sensitive matters, often glancing around to ensure privacy. His normal speaking voice maintains a servile tone appropriate for his cover, though bitter sarcasm occasionally slips through when discussing the Thalmor.', '* Survive long enough to see the Thalmor''s influence diminished or destroyed * Escape to Morrowind and establish a new life away from Thalmor influence * Avenge his family''s murder by contributing to the Thalmor''s downfall * Maintain his cover as long as possible to continue gathering valuable intelligence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('malkoran', 'Malkoran is a powerful Breton necromancer who has corrupted Meridia''s Temple, using the casualties of war to create an army of defiled shades. His mastery of frost magic and necromancy, combined with his considerable magical fortitude, makes him one of the most formidable practitioners of dark arts in Skyrim.', 'breton, mage, pale', '', '', 'sk_malewarlock', '', 'Originally trained in the Synod or College of Whispers, Malkoran''s obsession with necromancy led him down a darker path that eventually brought him to Skyrim. He discovered Meridia''s abandoned temple during the Civil War and saw an opportunity to harness the death surrounding him, turning the sacred site into his personal laboratory for necromantic experiments. His presence there is a deliberate affront to Meridia, whose hatred of the undead makes their conflict deeply personal.', 'Malkoran is arrogant and power-hungry, viewing the dead as mere tools for his ambitions and showing complete disdain for the sanctity of life or death. His willingness to desecrate a Daedric Prince''s temple demonstrates both his overwhelming hubris and his unshakeable confidence in his abilities. He is methodical and patient in his work, carefully cultivating his army of shades while maintaining a fortress-like control over his domain.', 'A tall, gaunt Breton with sunken features and pale skin that betrays years of working with dark magics. His eyes glow with an unnatural blue tinge, likely a side effect of extensive exposure to necromantic energies, and his body bears the subtle markings and scars typical of one who has undergone numerous magical rituals.', '* Meridia - Sworn enemy whose temple he has deliberately defiled * Corrupted Shades - His created servants, bound to his will * Local Warfare Victims - Sources for his necromantic experiments * Fellow Necromancers - Likely maintains distant professional contacts for knowledge exchange', 'Malkoran serves as both a necromancer and self-appointed master of Meridia''s corrupted temple. He maintains his position through force and dark magic, using the ongoing civil war as a constant source of new materials for his experiments while expanding his knowledge of necromancy through practical application.', '* Master-level destruction magic with particular expertise in frost spells * Advanced necromancy and corpse manipulation * Exceptional magical resistance and fortitude * Skilled in ward casting and magical defense * Ability to create and control multiple shades simultaneously * Knowledge of ritual magic and desecration techniques', 'Malkoran speaks with cold authority and academic precision, often using arcane terminology and showing contempt for those he deems inferior. His voice carries the weight of power and knowledge, though it''s tinged with the arrogance typical of those who have delved too deeply into forbidden arts.', '* Perfect the art of shade creation and establish a permanent army of the dead * Expand his necromantic knowledge beyond conventional limitations * Maintain control over Meridia''s temple as a symbol of his power * Potentially achieve a form of immortality through his experiments');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('malkus', 'Malkus is a formidable Orc vampire who serves Lord Harkon''s court with unwavering dedication to the vampire cause. As the only known Orcish vampire in Skyrim, he combines the natural strength of his race with vampiric powers, specializing in mind control and enthrallment of victims.', 'orc, haafingar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Originally a warrior from one of Skyrim''s Orc strongholds, Malkus was turned into a vampire and found purpose in Lord Harkon''s court. His exceptional willpower and natural Orcish resistance to magic likely contributed to his mastery of mental domination techniques, making him an invaluable asset for missions requiring the subjugation of powerful minds.', 'Malkus is methodical, patient, and ruthlessly efficient in pursuing his objectives. He takes pride in breaking down mental resistance through a combination of magical influence and psychological manipulation, demonstrating both cunning and cruelty in his methods. His Orcish heritage manifests in his direct approach to confrontation, though tempered by vampiric sophistication.', 'Malkus possesses the muscular build typical of Orcs, combined with the pale complexion and predatory features of a vampire. His prominent tusks and facial structure retain their Orcish characteristics, while his eyes glow with an unnatural vampiric hunger.', '* Lord Harkon - Superior and leader of the Volkihar vampire court * Dexion Evicus - Captive Moth Priest targeted for enthrallment * Vanik - Dawnguard agent and eventual killer (if siding with vampires) * Volkihar Vampire Court - Fellow servants of Lord Harkon', 'Malkus serves as a specialized operative within the Volkihar vampire court, focusing on missions requiring mental domination and the acquisition of valuable assets. His primary role involves capturing and enthralling powerful individuals who possess knowledge or abilities useful to Lord Harkon''s plans.', '* Master of mental domination and enthrallment magic * Skilled in destruction magic, particularly frost-based spells * Proficient in one-handed combat techniques * Expert in psychological manipulation and interrogation * Enhanced strength and endurance from both Orcish heritage and vampirism', 'Malkus speaks with a commanding and methodical tone, combining the harsh accent of Orcish speech with the refined manner of ancient vampires. His words are carefully chosen to wear down resistance, alternating between threatening growls and hypnotic persuasion.', '* Successfully enthrall the Moth Priest to serve vampire interests * Advance Lord Harkon''s plans for the Tyranny of the Sun * Prove himself as the most capable mental dominator in the vampire court * Maintain his unique status as the only Orcish vampire in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mallus_maccius', 'Mallus Maccius is a shrewd Imperial businessman who transforms from an indebted meadery worker to a successful merchant and Thieves Guild fence through cunning opportunism. His partnership with Maven Black-Briar and betrayal of his former employer Sabjorn demonstrates his calculating nature and determination to advance his station in life.', 'imperial, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally a merchant who fell on hard times, Mallus was forced to borrow money from Sabjorn, leading to what amounted to indentured servitude at Honningbrew Meadery. His resentment of Sabjorn''s harsh treatment eventually led him to collaborate with Maven Black-Briar and the Thieves Guild to orchestrate his employer''s downfall, resulting in his elevation to meadery manager.', 'Mallus is opportunistic, shrewd, and somewhat bitter from his experiences of financial hardship and mistreatment. He shows little loyalty except to those who can advance his interests, as demonstrated by his willingness to betray Sabjorn. Despite his cutthroat business sense, he maintains a professional demeanor and shows genuine appreciation to those who help him improve his station.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered appearance of someone who has spent years working in service. He maintains a neat, practical appearance befitting a businessman, though his years of manual labor under Sabjorn have left their mark.', '* Sabjorn - Former employer turned enemy who held Mallus''s debt over him * Maven Black-Briar - New employer and powerful patron who elevated his status * Thieves Guild - Criminal associates who helped him gain control of the meadery * Various Whiterun merchants - Business contacts maintained through his new position', 'Mallus serves as both the manager of the newly-renamed Black-Briar Meadery West and as the Thieves Guild fence in Whiterun Hold. He handles the day-to-day operations of the meadery while secretly facilitating the sale of stolen goods for the Guild.', '* Expert in business management and meadery operations * Skilled negotiator and fence for stolen goods * Proficient at maintaining a legitimate business front while conducting illegal operations * Basic combat abilities with a dagger for self-defense', 'Mallus speaks in a direct, business-like manner that can shift between servile and confident depending on his position of power in the conversation. His speech patterns reveal his merchant background, with a focus on transaction and opportunity.', '* Establish himself as a respected and wealthy merchant in Whiterun * Maintain and strengthen his profitable relationship with Maven Black-Briar * Expand the meadery''s operations under Black-Briar management * Build a network of reliable contacts for his fencing operations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('malthyr_elenil', 'Malthyr Elenil is a world-weary Dark Elf pawnbroker living in Windhelm''s impoverished Gray Quarter, working as a bartender at the New Gnisis Cornerclub. Despite his resentment towards Nordic discrimination, he maintains his position out of loyalty to his employer Ambarys Rendar and his fellow Dunmer, while harboring dreams of returning to Morrowind.', 'darkelf, merchant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Malthyr immigrated to Windhelm seeking refuge among his fellow Dunmer after the Red Mountain''s eruption displaced many Dark Elves. He found employment at the New Gnisis Cornerclub, rising to become Ambarys Rendar''s most trusted employee and designated successor, though the harsh reality of life in the Gray Quarter has left him disillusioned with his adopted home.', 'Malthyr is a bitter but dignified individual who maintains a veneer of formality despite his circumstances. While deeply resentful of Nordic prejudice and the squalid conditions forced upon his people, he remains pragmatic and loyal to his community, choosing to endure rather than abandon his responsibilities.', 'A typical Dunmer male with ashen gray skin and the characteristic red eyes of his race. His face shows signs of weariness and age, with sharp angular features common to Dark Elves. His posture, while proud, betrays years of working long hours in the cornerclub.', '* Ambarys Rendar - Employer and friend, trusts Malthyr to eventually take over the cornerclub * Brunwulf Free-Winter - Respects him as a potential advocate for Dunmer rights * Fellow Gray Quarter residents - Shares a bond of mutual hardship and community * Ulfric Stormcloak - Resents him for perpetuating Nordic discrimination * Nordic citizens - Generally distrustful due to years of discrimination', 'Works as a bartender and general helper at the New Gnisis Cornerclub, while also engaging in small-scale pawnbroking business on the side. He is designated to inherit management of the cornerclub should anything happen to the current owner.', '* Experienced bartender and business management abilities * Knowledgeable in appraising and trading goods as a pawnbroker * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Street-smart survival skills developed from life in the Gray Quarter', 'Speaks with a formal, slightly reserved manner typical of educated Dunmer, often using proper grammar and maintaining a dignified tone despite his circumstances. His bitterness occasionally seeps through in sardonic observations about life in Windhelm.', '* Improve living conditions for Dunmer in the Gray Quarter * Eventually return to Morrowind if circumstances permit * Successfully take over and maintain the New Gnisis Cornerclub when needed * Preserve Dunmer culture and dignity within Windhelm despite Nordic oppression');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('malur_seloth', 'Malur Seloth is a shrewd Dark Elf steward who has masterfully crafted a comfortable position in Winterhold by exploiting racial prejudices and false assumptions about his connection to the College. Through careful manipulation and strategic laziness, he maintains his status while doing minimal work, exemplifying the art of social engineering in Skyrim''s harsh political landscape.', 'darkelf, noble, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Malur likely fled west following the Red Mountain''s eruption, eventually settling in Winterhold where he recognized an opportunity to exploit local prejudices. Through careful social maneuvering and capitalizing on the widespread assumption that all Dark Elves are skilled mages, he secured the position of steward despite having no actual magical abilities or College connections.', 'Malur is fundamentally lazy and opportunistic, preferring to maintain his position through manipulation rather than honest work. He shows remarkable cunning in maintaining his facade of magical connections while avoiding actual responsibilities, and takes pleasure in the fear and respect his assumed status grants him. Despite his deceptive nature, he maintains just enough competence in his duties to avoid serious scrutiny.', 'A typical Dunmer with ashen gray skin and the characteristic red eyes of his race. His face shows signs of age with subtle wrinkles, though he maintains good posture to project authority. His build is average for a Dark Elf, neither particularly muscular nor frail.', '* Jarl of Winterhold - Employer who likely remains unaware of Malur''s true nature * Nelacar - Target of his schemes, particularly regarding the Staff of Arcane Authority * Thonjolf - Imperial housecarl who gives Malur special treatment due to assumed College connections * College of Winterhold Staff - No actual connections, though he maintains appearances of association * Winterhold Citizens - Maintains careful distance while exploiting their assumptions about his magical abilities', 'As steward of Winterhold, Malur is officially responsible for managing the Jarl''s household, maintaining records, and handling administrative duties. In practice, he performs the minimum necessary work to maintain his position while spending considerable time lounging around the town and avoiding actual responsibilities.', '* Expert in social manipulation and maintaining false appearances * Basic administrative capabilities necessary for steward duties * Proficient in avoiding work while appearing busy * Adequate speech and persuasion abilities * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense', 'Speaks with a dismissive and slightly arrogant tone, often using deflection and vague statements to maintain his mystique. His vocabulary is educated but not overly formal, helping him maintain the image of a sophisticated College associate while avoiding specific claims that could expose his deception.', '* Maintain his comfortable position as steward while doing as little work as possible * Continue exploiting the town''s assumptions about his College connections * Acquire items like the Staff of Arcane Authority to reinforce his false magical reputation * Avoid any situation that might expose his lack of magical ability or College connections');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('maluril', 'Maluril Ferano is a Dark Elf scholar obsessed with unlocking the secrets of Dwemer technology and power, conducting his research from within the dangerous ruins of Mzinchaleft. His academic pursuits mask a darker nature, as evidenced by his need for bandit protection and his status as a Dark Brotherhood target.', 'darkelf, scholar, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally trained as a mage, Maluril devoted his life to studying Dwemer artifacts and their potential for power. His research led him to establish a permanent residence in Mzinchaleft, where he surrounded himself with bandit protectors and accumulated an extensive collection of Dwemer relics. His past activities have earned him powerful enemies, though the exact nature of his transgressions remains unclear.', 'Maluril is an intelligent but paranoid individual, displaying both scholarly dedication and ruthless ambition in his pursuit of Dwemer knowledge. He maintains a facade of academic propriety while harboring darker intentions, as suggested by his journal entries and choice of criminal associates. His obsession with controlling Dwemer power has led him to become increasingly secretive and territorial about his research.', 'A typical Dunmer with ashen skin and the characteristic red eyes of his race, Maluril carries himself with the bearing of a scholar rather than a warrior. His frame is lean and typical of those who spend more time pursuing academic interests than physical training, though years of living in dangerous ruins have kept him reasonably fit.', '* Bandit Guards - Hired muscle who protect him and his research * Dark Brotherhood - Unknown enemies who have marked him for death * Dwemer Researchers - Competitive and often hostile relationships with rival scholars * Former Academic Colleagues - Burned bridges suggested by his exile to Mzinchaleft', 'Maluril serves as an independent Dwemer researcher and artifact collector, operating outside traditional academic institutions. His work involves both scholarly study and the practical application of Dwemer technology, though his methods and true intentions appear to be ethically questionable.', '* Proficient in destruction magic, particularly with fire-based attacks * Experienced in the study and manipulation of Dwemer artifacts * Basic combat abilities with conventional weapons * Academic knowledge of ancient Dwemer culture and technology * Survival skills necessary for living in dangerous ruins', 'Maluril speaks with the formal vocabulary of a scholar, though his tone often carries undertones of suspicion and territorial aggression. He frequently employs academic terminology when discussing Dwemer artifacts but can quickly shift to threatening language when he feels his research is threatened.', '* Unlock the secrets of Dwemer power and learn to control their ancient technology * Establish himself as a leading authority on Dwemer artifacts and culture * Protect his research and findings from rival scholars and thieves * Harness Dwemer technology for personal gain and power');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('malyn_varen', 'Malyn Varen was a brilliant but troubled Dark Elf sorcerer whose obsession with immortality and soul gem research led to his expulsion from the College of Winterhold. His desperate experiments with Azura''s Star ultimately resulted in his transformation into a soul-bound entity, trapped between life and death while requiring constant souls to maintain his existence.', 'darkelf, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally a respected instructor at the College of Winterhold, Malyn Varen''s research into soul gems became increasingly dangerous as he sought to escape a fatal disease. After being cursed by Azura for tampering with her artifact, his mental state deteriorated rapidly, leading to the death of a student and his subsequent exile. He retreated to Ilinalta''s Deep with his most devoted followers, where his experiments grew more desperate until he finally succeeded in binding himself to the damaged Star.', 'Malyn exhibits severe paranoia and megalomania, believing himself to have transcended mortality and defied the Daedric Lords themselves. His once-brilliant mind has been shattered by Azura''s curse and his own desperate actions, leaving him in a state of perpetual hunger for souls and delusional grandeur. Despite his madness, he retains enough cunning to maintain his realm within the Star and command loyal followers.', 'A gaunt Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, showing visible signs of his physical deterioration and madness. His body bears the marks of his desperate experiments and magical corruption, with an otherworldly pallor that speaks to his unnatural state of existence.', '* College of Winterhold - Former employer turned adversary after his exile * Loyal Students - Devoted followers who assisted his experiments and provided souls * Azura - Daedric Prince who cursed him for defiling her artifact * Nelacar - Former colleague who knows the truth about his experiments', 'Formerly a distinguished instructor at the College of Winterhold specializing in soul gem research and enchanting. After his exile, he became a rogue sorcerer conducting forbidden experiments in soul manipulation and immortality, eventually transforming into a soul-bound entity within Azura''s Star.', '* Master-level knowledge of soul gem mechanics and enchanting * Powerful destruction magic focusing on lightning and ice spells * Advanced understanding of alteration magic for self-protection * Expertise in necromancy and soul manipulation * Restoration magic proficiency for self-preservation', 'His speech patterns are erratic and unstable, alternating between scholarly eloquence and maniacal ranting. He frequently speaks in grandiose terms about his achievements and power, with a tendency to shift between lucid explanation and paranoid accusations.', '* Maintain his immortality within Azura''s Star at any cost * Continue collecting souls to sustain his existence * Perfect his understanding of soul manipulation and immortality * Defend his realm within the Star from any who would threaten it');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mani', 'Mani is a young Redguard who reluctantly relocated with his family from Hammerfell to operate Frostflow Lighthouse in Skyrim''s harsh northern coast. His tragic story ends in death at the hands of Falmer raiders, highlighting the dangers faced by settlers in Skyrim''s remote regions.', 'redguard, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Hammerfell, Mani lived a comfortable life until his family''s decision to relocate to Skyrim to take over the Frostflow Lighthouse operations. The dramatic change from Hammerfell''s warm climate to Skyrim''s harsh environment was a difficult adjustment for the young man, leading to his strong desire to return to his homeland.', 'Mani is characterized by his strong sense of family loyalty despite his personal unhappiness with their current situation. He exhibits traits of homesickness and mild rebellion against his circumstances, yet maintains a protective nature toward his family members, particularly his sister Sudi. His actions suggest a practical mindset tempered by youthful impetuousness.', 'As a Redguard, Mani possesses the characteristic dark skin and athletic build common to his people. He likely maintains the traditional Redguard custom of keeping his hair closely cropped, with strong, defined features reflecting his youth and vigor.', '* Habd - Father and lighthouse keeper, whom Mani was waiting to return from town * Ramati - Mother, killed in the Falmer attack * Sudi - Younger sister, shared the same tragic fate in the Frostflow Abyss * Local Nords - Limited social connections due to recent arrival and remote location', 'Mani assists his family in operating and maintaining Frostflow Lighthouse, helping with daily tasks and lighthouse keeping duties. His role includes helping to maintain the beacon fire and assisting with general upkeep of the facility.', '* Basic combat training typical of Redguard youth * Practical knowledge of lighthouse operation and maintenance * Survival skills necessary for life in harsh climates * Familiar with basic weapon handling, particularly with daggers', 'Mani speaks with the distinct accent of a Hammerfell native, his tone often carrying undertones of homesickness and mild frustration. His manner of speech likely reflects his youth and education, using direct and straightforward language typical of Redguard culture.', '* Return to Hammerfell and resume his previous life * Ensure his family''s safety and well-being despite his personal dissatisfaction * Maintain family unity while seeking opportunities to convince them to leave Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('maramal', 'Maramal is a devoted priest of Mara who serves as the primary religious authority at the Temple of Mara in Riften. He is renowned throughout Skyrim as the only official who can perform marriage ceremonies, acting as both a spiritual leader and guardian of matrimonial traditions while spreading Mara''s message of love and compassion.', 'redguard, priest, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Hammerfell, Maramal discovered his calling to Mara''s priesthood at a young age. He traveled to Skyrim to study at the Temple of Mara in Riften, eventually rising to become one of its senior priests through his unwavering dedication and compassionate nature. His deep understanding of Mara''s teachings and genuine desire to help others has made him a respected figure in Riften''s religious community.', 'Maramal is gentle, patient, and deeply compassionate, embodying the virtues of the goddess he serves. He maintains an unwavering optimism even in Riften''s corrupt environment, believing in the transformative power of love and marriage. Though some may mock his earnest preaching, he remains steadfast in his mission to spread Mara''s teachings, showing particular patience with skeptics and those in need of guidance.', 'A middle-aged Redguard man with dark skin and weathered features that reflect years of devoted service. His face shows gentle laugh lines around his eyes and mouth, suggesting a lifetime of offering kind smiles to those seeking guidance. He carries himself with a dignified but approachable bearing typical of experienced clergy.', '* Dinya Balu - Beloved wife and fellow priest of Mara * Temple Initiates - Mentor and spiritual guide to new priests * Riften Citizens - Respected religious authority and counselor * Maven Black-Briar - Maintains cautious diplomatic relations as a prominent city figure * Laila Law-Giver - Official religious advisor to the Jarl''s court', 'Maramal serves as the senior priest at the Temple of Mara, where he performs marriage ceremonies, offers spiritual counseling, and oversees charitable works. He manages the temple''s daily operations, including organizing aid for the poor and sick, while also serving as the primary authority on matters of marriage throughout Skyrim.', '* Expert in religious rites and ceremonies, particularly marriage rituals * Proficient in Restoration magic and protective wards * Capable wielder of magical staves for self-defense * Skilled orator and preacher * Experienced counselor and mediator for couples and families', 'Maramal speaks with a gentle, measured tone that carries both authority and compassion, often using formal religious language interwoven with practical advice. His manner of speech is consistently warm and encouraging, though he can adopt a more commanding presence when preaching or performing ceremonies.', '* Spread Mara''s teachings of love and compassion throughout Skyrim * Maintain the sacred traditions of marriage and help couples find lasting happiness * Combat Riften''s corruption through charitable works and spiritual guidance * Expand the Temple''s influence and ability to help those in need');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('marcurio', 'Marcurio is a talented and self-assured Imperial destruction mage who works as a mercenary spellsword in Riften. Known for his theatrical personality and mastery of destructive magic, he offers his considerable arcane abilities to adventurers willing to meet his price while maintaining a permanent residence at the Bee and Barb inn.', 'imperial, mage, rift, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and educated in Cyrodiil, Marcurio likely received formal training at the Arcane University or a similar institution where he developed his expertise in destruction magic. He eventually made his way to Skyrim, choosing to ply his trade as a spell-sword in Riften rather than pursue a traditional academic career at the College of Winterhold, suggesting a preference for practical application of magic over theoretical study.', 'Marcurio is remarkably confident, often bordering on arrogant, with a flair for dramatic declarations about his magical prowess. He possesses a dry wit and sharp intellect, frequently making sardonic observations about his surroundings and companions. Despite his theatrical nature, he demonstrates genuine loyalty to those who earn his respect and takes pride in his reliability as a hired companion.', 'A tall, lean Imperial man with sharp features typical of his race, sporting dark hair and an expertly maintained goatee. His bearing is proud and dignified, with the practiced posture of a trained mage, and his eyes often gleam with intellectual curiosity.', '* Keerava - Business relationship with the Bee and Barb''s owner who provides his lodging * Talen-Jei - Friendly acquaintance and fellow regular at the Bee and Barb * College of Winterhold - Maintains distance despite magical ability, suggesting possible past conflict or philosophical differences * Local Thieves Guild - Cautious coexistence, neither antagonistic nor cooperative', 'Marcurio works as a freelance spellsword, offering his services as a magical mercenary to travelers and adventurers passing through Riften. He maintains a semi-permanent residence at the Bee and Barb inn, using it as a base of operations while between contracts.', '* Master-level destruction magic, particularly proficient with lightning spells * Significant expertise in defensive magic including wards and flesh spells * Competent restoration magic abilities for healing and undead turning * Adequate skill with daggers as backup weapons * Tactical combat awareness and battlefield positioning', 'Speaks with a cultured Imperial accent and employs sophisticated vocabulary, often delivering witty remarks with theatrical flair. His speech patterns reveal both his education and his tendency toward showmanship, frequently emphasizing his magical expertise.', '* Build a reputation as one of Skyrim''s premier magical mercenaries * Accumulate wealth and knowledge through adventuring * Find a worthy partner who appreciates his talents and ambition * Eventually establish his own magical enterprise or school');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('margret', 'Margret is an Imperial spy posing as a wealthy merchant''s sister from Cyrodiil, secretly investigating the Silver-Blood family''s control over Markarth. Her seemingly naive and ditzy demeanor masks her true identity as a skilled intelligence operative working directly for General Tullius to gather information about the city''s political landscape.', 'nord, imperial, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in the Imperial City, Margret was recruited into Imperial intelligence operations at a young age due to her natural talent for appearing harmless and gathering information. She developed a cover identity as a merchant''s sister and has successfully completed several missions across Tamriel before being assigned to investigate Markarth''s power structure and the valuable Treasury House deed.', 'Margret deliberately projects an air of naive innocence and slight confusion to deflect suspicion, playing the role of a somewhat scattered shopping enthusiast. Beneath this carefully crafted persona lies a sharp, observant mind trained in espionage and information gathering. She maintains her cover even under extreme stress, such as during the assassination attempt.', 'Margret is a tall Nord woman with typical Nordic features, though her time in Cyrodiil has softened her appearance somewhat. She maintains a deliberately unremarkable appearance to avoid drawing attention, with medium-length light brown hair and an average build that helps her blend into crowds.', '* General Tullius - Direct superior who assigned her the Markarth mission * Imperial Intelligence Network - Active member and field operative * Silver-Blood Family - Investigation targets * Fictional Sister in Cyrodiil - Cover story relationship used to maintain her merchant facade', 'While publicly claiming to be a merchant''s sister on a shopping trip, Margret is actually an undercover Imperial intelligence operative. Her true mission involves gathering information about Markarth''s political structure and attempting to acquire the Treasury House deed for the Empire.', '* Expert in maintaining cover identities and deceptive roleplay * Trained in information gathering and covert observation * Competent in basic self-defense and evasion techniques * Skilled in social manipulation and extracting information through casual conversation', 'Margret speaks in a deliberately breathy, somewhat scattered manner with frequent pauses and expressions of confusion to reinforce her cover identity. She maintains a slight Imperial City accent while carefully avoiding any vocabulary that might reveal her true education and training.', '* Acquire the Markarth Treasury deed for General Tullius and the Empire * Gather intelligence on the Silver-Blood family''s influence in the Reach * Complete her mission without compromising her cover identity * Survive the increasing dangers of political intrigue in Markarth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('marise_aravel', 'Marise Aravel is a skilled Dark Elf merchant who has mastered the rare art of food preservation using ice wraith teeth, a technique she learned during her travels through Hammerfell. She maintains one of the most respected food stalls in Riften''s marketplace, known for her exceptionally fresh produce and meats that remain unspoiled far longer than her competitors'' wares.', 'darkelf, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Marise traveled extensively before settling in Riften, during which time she spent significant time in Hammerfell where she learned her signature preservation technique from a butcher in Elinhir. Her merchant background and extensive travel experience have given her both business acumen and a wealth of knowledge about various regional cooking and preservation methods, setting her apart from typical market vendors.', 'Marise is hardworking, innovative, and takes immense pride in the quality of her goods. She maintains a friendly but professional demeanor with customers and fellow merchants alike, though she remains cautious about sharing her trade secrets. Her attitude toward the Thieves Guild reveals a strong moral compass and disdain for criminal behavior, suggesting she values honest work and fair dealing.', 'As a Dark Elf, Marise has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of her race, with sharp, angular features typical of mer. She maintains a neat, clean appearance befitting a food merchant, with well-groomed hair and clean hands essential for handling food products.', '* Fellow Merchants - Maintains cordial professional relationships with other market vendors * Shadr - Shows friendly interest, willing to share drinks at the Bee and Barb * Thieves Guild - Holds strong negative opinions about their presence in Riften * Maven Black-Briar - Keeps cautiously respectful relations as required for business in Riften * Drifa - Regular market interaction as fellow vendor', 'Marise operates a successful fresh food stall in Riften''s marketplace, specializing in preserved meats and produce. Her unique preservation technique using ice wraith teeth sets her business apart from other vendors, allowing her to offer superior quality products to her customers.', '* Expert knowledge of food preservation techniques, especially using ice wraith teeth * Skilled merchant with strong bargaining and customer service abilities * Proficient in basic food preparation and storage methods * Capable of identifying quality produce and meats * Basic self-defense abilities with a dagger', 'Marise speaks in a professional yet approachable manner, often calling out to promote her wares with pride and enthusiasm. Her speech patterns reflect her merchant background, mixing friendly banter with business-oriented dialogue.', '* Maintain and expand her successful market business in Riften * Secure a reliable supply of ice wraith teeth to continue her unique preservation method * Build a reputation as Riften''s premier food merchant * Eventually pass on her preservation knowledge to a worthy apprentice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('markus', 'Markus is a seasoned Nord carriage driver stationed at Heljarchen Hall who provides safe passage through Skyrim''s dangerous territories. A former soldier turned transportation specialist, he combines his combat expertise with extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s geography to ensure his passengers reach their destinations unharmed.', 'nord, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh climate of the Pale, Markus served in the Stormcloak army during his younger years before seeking a more peaceful yet purposeful occupation. His military experience and intimate knowledge of Skyrim''s roadways made him an ideal candidate for specialized carriage services, leading him to establish his operation at Heljarchen Hall.', 'Markus exhibits a professional demeanor tempered with Nordic warmth and hospitality, making him well-liked by his regular passengers. He maintains a vigilant attitude during travels, drawing from his military experience to anticipate and avoid potential dangers, while his natural storytelling abilities make him an engaging travel companion.', 'A sturdy Nord in his mid-forties with weather-worn features that speak to years of outdoor work. His muscular build reflects his military background and the physical demands of managing horses and cargo, while his clear blue eyes retain the sharp alertness of a trained warrior.', '* The Player - Primary employer and frequent traveling companion * Heljarchen Hall Staff - Cooperative working relationship with other homestead workers * Local Merchants - Maintains friendly connections for horse supplies and carriage maintenance * Former Stormcloak Comrades - Occasional contacts from military service days', 'Markus serves as a professional carriage driver based at Heljarchen Hall, specializing in safe transport across Skyrim''s nine holds. His services include both scheduled routes and private charter transportation, with additional expertise in cargo security and route planning.', '* Expert horsemanship and carriage handling in various weather conditions * Skilled warrior proficient with one-handed weapons and shield combat * Extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s geography and safe travel routes * Advanced survival skills including weather prediction and wilderness navigation * Basic armor maintenance and horse care expertise', 'Speaks with a traditional Nordic accent, using clear, direct language enriched with occasional historical references and travel anecdotes. His tone remains professional yet friendly, often sharing relevant geographical or historical information during journeys.', '* Maintain and possibly expand his carriage service to better serve Skyrim''s travelers * Ensure the safety and satisfaction of all his passengers * Eventually train an apprentice to carry on his professional legacy * Save enough gold to retire comfortably in one of Skyrim''s major cities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mathies', 'Mathies is a hardworking Nord farmer in Falkreath whose life was shattered by the brutal murder of his young daughter Lavinia at the hands of Sinding. Despite this devastating tragedy, he maintains his farm alongside his Imperial wife Indara, embodying the resilience of common folk in Skyrim while carrying the weight of unimaginable loss.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath Hold, Mathies established himself as a respected farmer, eventually taking over operations at Corpselight Farm. He married Indara Caerellia, proving through their union that Nord-Imperial cooperation was possible even during times of civil strife. Their happiness was complete with the birth of their daughter Lavinia, until tragedy struck when she was killed by a laborer named Sinding before her tenth winter.', 'Mathies is a gentle, hardworking soul whose natural kindness persists even through profound grief. He maintains a philosophical outlook on life, believing in cooperation between races and staying neutral in political conflicts. Though deeply wounded by his daughter''s death, he finds solace in routine work and spiritual guidance, demonstrating remarkable resilience in the face of tragedy.', 'A weathered Nord of average height with the sturdy build typical of those who work the land. His hands are callused from years of farming, and his face bears the creases of both laughter and sorrow. His appearance reflects his profession and the hardships he''s endured, while maintaining the dignified bearing of a respectable townsman.', '* Indara Caerellia - Beloved wife and farming partner who shares his grief over their daughter * Lavinia - Deceased daughter whose memory he cherishes and mourns * Sinding - The murderer of his daughter, whom he views with confusion and horror * Runil - Trusted friend and spiritual advisor who helps him cope with loss * Falkreath Townspeople - Sympathetic neighbors who respect his dignity in grief', 'Mathies is the owner and primary worker of Corpselight Farm, one of Falkreath''s main agricultural operations. He maintains a strict daily routine of working the fields for twelve hours, followed by evenings at the Dead Man''s Drink, demonstrating his commitment to maintaining productivity despite personal tragedy.', '* Expert farmer with deep knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Capable physical laborer with stamina for long hours of fieldwork * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Animal husbandry knowledge learned from working alongside his wife', 'Mathies speaks in gentle, measured tones that carry an underlying current of melancholy. His vocabulary is simple but thoughtful, reflecting both his farming background and his contemplative nature.', '* Maintain Corpselight Farm''s productivity despite personal hardship * Honor his daughter''s memory through continued dedication to his work * Support his wife through their shared grief while preserving their marriage * Foster understanding between Nords and Imperials through his own example');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('matlara', 'Matlara is a Nord woman and devoted mother who lived in Helgen with her family before its destruction by Alduin. A victim of the dragon attack that marked the beginning of Skyrim''s dragon crisis, her tragic death alongside her husband Torolf left their son Haming orphaned.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Matlara settled in the frontier town of Helgen where she built a life with her husband Torolf. She was known in the community for her dedication to family life and was present during the attempted execution of both Ulfric Stormcloak and the future Dragonborn, witnessing firsthand the return of Alduin.', 'Matlara was a protective mother who prioritized her family''s wellbeing above all else. Her presence at the execution despite its grim nature suggests a sense of civic duty and community involvement typical of Nord culture. Even in her final moments, she demonstrated remarkable courage in the face of unprecedented danger.', 'Matlara possessed the hardy build and strong features characteristic of Nord women. She had the fair complexion common to her race, with a face weathered by Skyrim''s harsh climate and the demands of frontier life.', '* Torolf - Beloved husband who died alongside her in the dragon attack * Haming - Young son who survived the attack on Helgen * Helgen Townspeople - Part of the close-knit community before its destruction', 'As a resident of Helgen, Matlara likely contributed to the household through domestic duties and possibly local trade. Her clothing suggests she may have been involved in farming or other agricultural work common to frontier settlements.', '* Basic combat proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Domestic skills including cooking and household management * Agricultural knowledge typical of Skyrim''s farming communities', 'Matlara likely spoke with the distinctive Nordic accent common to Skyrim''s natives. Her dialogue would have reflected the practical, straightforward nature typical of Nord women.', '* Ensure the safety and wellbeing of her son Haming * Maintain a stable family life in Helgen * Support her community and uphold Nord traditions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('maul', 'Maul is a formidable Nord enforcer who serves as Maven Black-Briar''s trusted right-hand man in Riften, wielding both physical intimidation and strategic intelligence to protect the family''s interests. A former Thieves Guild member turned personal enforcer, he maintains a complex network of connections throughout Riften''s criminal underworld while ensuring the Black-Briars'' dominance remains unchallenged.', 'nord, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Riften, Maul and his brother Dirge became involved with the Thieves Guild at a young age, learning the arts of intimidation and information gathering. His exceptional loyalty and strategic mind caught Maven Black-Briar''s attention, leading to his promotion from common thief to her personal enforcer and confidant.', 'Maul is calculating, intimidating, and fiercely loyal to the Black-Briar family. He maintains a gruff, no-nonsense demeanor that masks a shrewd intelligence, using both physical presence and careful information control to maintain order. Despite his threatening exterior, he demonstrates pragmatism in dealing with useful allies while remaining ruthless against those who threaten his employers.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with strong Nordic features and an imposing physical presence. His face bears several scars from his years of enforcer work, and his stern expression and watchful eyes reflect years of experience in intimidation and combat.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Employer and primary loyalty, serves as her right-hand man * Dirge - Brother and fellow enforcer, maintains close familial bond * Thieves Guild - Former member who maintains valuable connections * Dark Brotherhood - Professional contact through Maven''s connections * Brynjolf - Former colleague from Thieves Guild days', 'Maul serves as Maven Black-Briar''s personal enforcer and intelligence gatherer, overseeing security for the Black-Briar family''s interests throughout Riften. If Maven becomes Jarl, he is elevated to the position of her housecarl, though his actual duties remain largely unchanged.', '* Expert in intimidation and information gathering * Skilled in close combat and weapon use, particularly with daggers * Advanced knowledge of Riften''s criminal networks and political landscape * Proficient in security assessment and threat detection * Strategic thinking and tactical planning', 'Speaks in a gruff, threatening manner with direct and concise statements designed to intimidate. Uses simple but effective language that leaves no room for misinterpretation, often delivering warnings and threats with a cold, calculated tone.', '* Maintain and expand the Black-Briar family''s influence in Riften * Protect Maven Black-Briar''s interests at all costs * Keep potential threats to the Black-Briars under constant surveillance * Strengthen his position as Maven''s most trusted enforcer');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('maurice_jondrelle', 'Maurice Jondrelle is a devout Breton priest and pilgrim of Kynareth who travels Skyrim seeking sacred places of natural beauty. His spiritual journey leads him to Whiterun''s Temple of Kynareth, where his dedication to preserving nature''s sanctity becomes evident in his passionate concern for the withered Gildergreen.', 'breton, priest, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Maurice was drawn to the worship of Kynareth from an early age, finding spiritual connection in nature''s beauty and raw power. He eventually took vows as a priest and began a life of pilgrimage, traveling to various sacred sites dedicated to the Goddess of Air and Nature. His journey ultimately brought him to Skyrim, seeking the legendary Gildergreen of Whiterun.', 'Maurice is a peaceful and contemplative soul who abhors violence, preferring diplomatic solutions and natural harmony. He can be passionate and outspoken when defending nature''s sanctity, as shown in his confrontation with Danica Pure-Spring about the Gildergreen''s neglect. Despite his gentle nature, he possesses unwavering determination when pursuing his spiritual goals.', 'Maurice is a middle-aged Breton of average height with a lean, ascetic build shaped by years of traveling on foot. His face shows the weathering of one who spends much time outdoors, with clear eyes that reflect his spiritual devotion.', '* Danica Pure-Spring - Fellow priest of Kynareth, though they disagree on priorities regarding the Gildergreen * The Dragonborn - Potential ally in the quest to restore the Gildergreen * Eldergleam Sanctuary Pilgrims - Fellow worshippers he may join if peaceful solution is chosen', 'Maurice serves as a wandering priest of Kynareth, undertaking pilgrimages to sacred natural sites and spreading the goddess''s teachings. His role combines elements of religious devotion, environmental stewardship, and spiritual guidance for fellow followers of Kynareth.', '* Extensive knowledge of natural theology and Kynareth''s teachings * Experienced wilderness traveler and survivor * Diplomatic abilities and peaceful conflict resolution * Basic restoration magic typical of Breton heritage * Herbalism and natural medicine knowledge', 'Maurice speaks with careful consideration and reverence, often using nature-based metaphors and religious terminology. His tone is gentle but can become impassioned when discussing matters of faith or environmental preservation.', '* Restore and protect sacred natural sites dedicated to Kynareth * Guide others to appreciate and preserve nature''s beauty * Establish permanent residence at the Eldergleam Sanctuary to serve as its guardian * Spread Kynareth''s teachings throughout Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('maven_black-briar', 'Maven Black-Briar is the ruthless and calculating matriarch of Riften''s most powerful family, wielding influence through a complex web of legitimate businesses and criminal enterprises. Her iron grip on the city''s economy and politics is maintained through careful manipulation of both legal and illegal channels, backed by her connections to the Thieves Guild and Dark Brotherhood.', 'nord, noble, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_maven', '', 'Born into wealth but ambitious for more, Maven built the Black-Briar empire through a combination of shrewd business acumen and ruthless elimination of competition. She transformed her family''s meadery into a dominant economic force while simultaneously cultivating ties with criminal organizations to extend her reach beyond legal boundaries. Her rise to power included strategic political alliances and the careful grooming of her children to maintain the family''s legacy.', 'Maven is coldly calculating, arrogant, and utterly without scruples in pursuing her goals. She maintains a veneer of aristocratic sophistication while harboring a ruthless streak that makes her feared throughout the Rift. Her manipulative nature and sharp intelligence allow her to maintain control through a careful balance of intimidation, bribery, and political maneuvering.', 'Maven is a mature Nord woman with sharp, aristocratic features and an imperious bearing that commands attention. Her face bears the subtle signs of aging, though she maintains a refined appearance befitting her status. She carries herself with perfect posture and controlled movements that project authority and power.', '* Hemming Black-Briar - Eldest son and heir, groomed to continue the family legacy * Sibbi Black-Briar - Imprisoned son whose violent tendencies she keeps in check * Ingun Black-Briar - Daughter whose alchemical interests she tolerates but doesn''t support * Jarl Laila Law-Giver - Political ally despite ideological differences * Thieves Guild - Strategic criminal partners who help maintain her power * Dark Brotherhood - Feared associates who handle her more permanent problems * Maul - Trusted enforcer and right-hand man * Maven''s Competitors - Numerous enemies who have either been ruined or eliminated', 'Maven serves as the unofficial power behind Riften''s throne, controlling both legitimate businesses and criminal enterprises. She oversees the Black-Briar Meadery empire while maintaining various other business interests throughout the city. If the Imperial Legion takes control of the Rift, she assumes the official position of Jarl.', '* Expert in business management and economic manipulation * Skilled in political maneuvering and information gathering * Proficient in basic destruction magic including Lightning Bolt and Sparks * Accomplished negotiator and intimidator * Strategic mastermind with extensive knowledge of both legal and criminal operations', 'Maven speaks with a refined, aristocratic manner that barely conceals her contemptuous nature. Her speech is precise and often condescending, frequently employing subtle threats and demonstrations of her power through carefully chosen words.', '* Maintain and expand the Black-Briar family''s dominance over Riften''s economic and political spheres * Secure her legacy through careful manipulation of her children''s roles in the family business * Strengthen her alliance with the Thieves Guild while maintaining plausible deniability * Eventually secure the position of Jarl through either political maneuvering or Imperial victory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('maximian_axius', 'Maximian Axius was a dedicated Imperial soldier stationed at Fort Frostmoth under General Falx Carius, whose life came to a tragic end during the Red Mountain eruption. A man of unwavering duty and deep familial devotion, his final days were spent writing heartfelt letters to his beloved wife Selina while trapped within the fort''s walls.', 'imperial, warrior, solstheim, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Maximian joined the Imperial Legion seeking to serve the Empire with honor and provide for his growing family. His military career led him to be stationed at Fort Frostmoth on Solstheim, where he served with distinction under General Falx Carius until the catastrophic eruption of Red Mountain in 4E 5 sealed his fate.', 'Maximian was characterized by his strong sense of duty, loyalty, and familial devotion, as evidenced by his final letters. He maintained his composure and dignity even in the face of certain death, showing remarkable strength of character. His writings reveal a tender-hearted family man who balanced his military obligations with deep emotional connections to his wife and children.', 'A well-built Imperial male with the hardened physique of a career soldier. His years of military service likely left him with the straight-backed posture and disciplined bearing typical of Legion veterans.', '* Selina Axius - Beloved wife and mother of his children * Siricus Axius - Son * Atia Axius - Daughter * General Falx Carius - Respected commanding officer at Fort Frostmoth * Fellow Fort Frostmoth Garrison Members - Brothers-in-arms', 'Maximian served as an Imperial soldier in the Fort Frostmoth garrison, carrying out defensive and peacekeeping duties on the island of Solstheim. His position required maintaining order, protecting Imperial interests, and following the direct commands of General Falx Carius.', '* Trained in standard Imperial Legion combat techniques and formations * Proficient with sword and shield as per Legion training * Experienced in cold weather survival and fortress defense * Capable of maintaining military discipline under extreme conditions', 'Based on his letters, Maximian spoke with the formal dignity of an Imperial soldier while maintaining warmth and tenderness when addressing family. His writing suggests he was well-educated and articulate, typical of Imperial Legion officers.', '* Protect and provide for his family through honorable military service * Serve the Empire with distinction at Fort Frostmoth * Return home to his wife and children after his tour of duty * Maintain his duty and honor until the very end');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('meden_maren', 'Meden Maren is a dedicated Dark Elf miner in Raven Rock who exemplifies the hardworking spirit of his people during Solstheim''s economic recovery. Having endured the mine''s closure and subsequent hardships, he now serves as an enthusiastic representative of House Redoran''s successful efforts to restore prosperity to the island.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Solstheim, Meden Maren has spent most of his adult life working in Raven Rock Mine, following in the footsteps of generations of Dunmer miners. When the mine closed, he struggled to provide for his family, likely taking odd jobs around Raven Rock while maintaining hope for the mine''s reopening. His loyalty to House Redoran was rewarded when they successfully restored the mine''s operations, allowing him to return to his true calling.', 'Meden is an optimistic and grateful individual who takes genuine pride in his work and appreciates the stability it provides. Despite the typical Dunmer reservation toward outsiders, he shows unusual warmth and openness to newcomers, particularly those who contribute to Raven Rock''s wellbeing. His strong work ethic and positive attitude make him a valuable presence in the mine, often lifting the spirits of his fellow miners.', 'Like most Dunmer, Meden has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race, with pronounced cheekbones and slightly pointed ears. His body is lean but muscular from years of physical labor, with calloused hands and a slightly stooped posture common among career miners.', '* House Redoran - Loyal supporter and grateful employee * Fellow Miners - Maintains positive working relationships with colleagues * Family - Has dependents he provides for through his mining work * Crescius Caerellius - Respects the former mine owner''s family legacy', 'Meden works as a senior miner in Raven Rock Mine, specializing in ebony ore extraction. His responsibilities include maintaining mining equipment, identifying promising veins of ore, and ensuring safe mining practices are followed.', '* Expert in ebony ore identification and extraction techniques * Proficient with mining tools and equipment maintenance * Knowledge of mine safety procedures and cave navigation * Basic understanding of Dunmer mining traditions and practices', 'Speaks with the distinctive accent of Morrowind Dunmer, but maintains a warmer and more welcoming tone than most of his kin. His speech often includes references to the mine''s condition and expressions of gratitude toward House Redoran.', '* Continue providing stable income for his family through honest work * Help maintain Raven Rock Mine''s productivity and safety * Support House Redoran''s efforts to restore Raven Rock to prosperity * Pass on his mining knowledge to younger workers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('medresi_dran', 'Medresi Dran is an ambitious Dark Elf treasure hunter who leads an excavation at Angarvunde in search of legendary artifacts of power. Her overwhelming greed and reckless pursuit of wealth ultimately lead to her demise when she attempts to claim the ruins'' treasures for herself.', 'darkelf, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Medresi established herself as a professional treasure hunter and expedition leader in Skyrim, focusing on Nordic ruins. She spent considerable time researching Angarvunde''s legends and assembled a team of workers to excavate the site, investing significant resources into the operation before encountering the draugr that scattered her workforce.', 'Medresi is cunning, manipulative, and driven by an insatiable greed that clouds her judgment. She displays a condescending attitude toward others, viewing them as tools to achieve her goals rather than equals. Her impatience and arrogance lead her to underestimate the dangers of ancient Nordic ruins, despite her experience as a treasure hunter.', 'A typical Dunmer with ashen gray skin and the characteristic red eyes of her race. She has sharp, angular features common to Dark Elves and maintains a fit physique necessary for her profession as a treasure hunter.', '* Hired Workers - Former excavation team who fled after discovering draugr * Player Character - Temporary alliance of convenience * Local Nordic Scholars - Academic contacts who provided information about Angarvunde * Rival Treasure Hunters - Competitive relationships with other artifact seekers', 'Professional treasure hunter and expedition leader specializing in Nordic ruins. She finances and organizes excavations, hires workers, and researches potential sites containing valuable artifacts.', '* Experienced archaeologist with knowledge of Nordic ruins and their layouts * Capable of organizing and leading excavation teams * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense * Knowledgeable in ancient Nordic lore and artifacts * Skilled at negotiation and manipulation', 'Speaks with a confident, slightly haughty tone typical of educated Dunmer, often using condescending language when addressing others. Her vocabulary reflects her education and profession, frequently referencing archaeological terms and ancient Nordic history.', '* Claim the legendary treasure of Angarvunde for herself * Build her reputation as a successful treasure hunter * Amass significant wealth through the discovery of valuable artifacts * Establish herself as a prominent figure in Skyrim''s archaeological community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('meeko', 'Meeko is a loyal and brave dog companion who lost his Nord master and now seeks a new purpose alongside the Dragonborn. Despite his tragic past, he maintains an unwavering spirit and proves himself to be not just a pet, but a valuable ally in combat and exploration throughout Skyrim.', 'animal', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally belonging to a Nord who lived in a remote shack south of Solitude, Meeko was left alone after his master''s death. He spent an unknown period guarding his master''s body and the shack, refusing to abandon his post until finding a worthy new companion. His loyalty and intelligence suggest he may have received specialized training, possibly from guards or hunters.', 'Meeko exhibits exceptional loyalty and bravery, willing to face any danger to protect his companion. Despite his past trauma, he maintains a playful and friendly demeanor, showing particular gentleness with children while remaining fierce in combat. His intelligence is notably above average for a dog, demonstrated by his ability to lead travelers to his former master''s shack and understand complex commands.', 'Meeko is a robust Nordic hunting dog with a thick double coat suited to Skyrim''s harsh climate. His muscular build and alert posture suggest both his hunting background and combat capability, while his expressive eyes convey remarkable intelligence.', '* Former Nord Master - Deceased owner whom Meeko loyally guarded even after death * The Dragonborn - Potential new master and companion * Children of the Dragonborn - Possible new family members if adopted as a house pet * Other Followers - Cooperative companion who works well alongside the Dragonborn''s other allies', 'Meeko serves as both a loyal companion and combat ally to those who earn his trust. His natural hunting instincts and combat abilities make him an effective guardian and fighter, while his friendly nature allows him to double as a beloved house pet for families.', '* Exceptional combat prowess against various enemies * Natural tracking and hunting abilities * Remarkable intelligence and ability to understand complex commands * Strong protective instincts and awareness of surroundings', 'While unable to speak human language, Meeko communicates through a combination of barks, whines, and body language that effectively convey his intentions and emotions. His responses often seem to demonstrate understanding of human speech far beyond that of an ordinary dog.', '* Find a worthy new master to serve and protect * Defend his companion against any threats they may face * Maintain the memory of his former master through continued loyal service * Provide companionship and protection to a new family if adopted as a house pet');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('melaran', 'Melaran is a sophisticated High Elf mage serving as an advisor and personal wizard to Thane Erikur in Solitude, though he views his position with barely concealed disdain. His presence at the Blue Palace and connection to Solitude''s political elite suggests a calculated career move rather than a position of passion.', 'highelf', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally trained in magic arts likely at the Crystal Tower or similar Altmer institution before its destruction, Melaran made his way to Skyrim seeking opportunity among the province''s nobility. He secured his position with Erikur through his magical expertise and understanding of political maneuvering, though the exact circumstances of their arrangement remain unclear.', 'Melaran exhibits the typical Altmer traits of superiority and intellectual elitism, particularly evident in his dismissive attitude toward most humans. He maintains a carefully measured demeanor that balances professional courtesy with thinly veiled contempt, showing particular respect only for those who demonstrate magical aptitude. Despite his apparent disdain for his position, he is pragmatic enough to recognize the benefits of his comfortable arrangement.', 'Tall and slender with the characteristic golden skin and angular features of his Altmer race. His face bears the sharp, hawkish features common to High Elves, with eyes that hold the typical golden hue of his people. His bearing is elegant and practiced, reflecting his noble upbringing and magical training.', '* Erikur - Employer and Thane of Solitude, whom Melaran serves with professional dedication but personal disdain * Sybille Stentor - Fellow mage whom he respects for her magical prowess despite her being human * Solitude Court - Maintains professional relationships with various members of the court * Blue Palace Staff - Keeps a cordial but distant relationship with other palace workers', 'Serves as personal wizard and advisor to Thane Erikur, handling magical affairs and providing counsel on various matters. His position grants him access to the Blue Palace and Solitude''s political sphere, where he spends considerable time observing court proceedings and maintaining his employer''s interests.', '* Accomplished mage with particular expertise in magical theory and enchanting * Skilled in court etiquette and political navigation * Proficient in defensive magic and magical protection * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Experienced in household management and advisory duties', 'Speaks in a refined, educated manner with careful enunciation and occasional condescension. His vocabulary reflects his educated background, and he often employs subtle sarcasm when addressing those he considers beneath him.', '* Maintain his comfortable position while seeking opportunities for advancement in Solitude''s court * Expand his magical knowledge and possibly gain influence equal to the court wizard * Eventually secure a more prestigious position worthy of his perceived talents * Study the dragons'' return from an academic perspective');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('melka', 'Melka is a uniquely cooperative hagraven who, despite her species'' typically hostile nature, seeks alliance with mortals after being betrayed and imprisoned by a rival hagraven. She demonstrates unusual restraint and calculation in pursuing her revenge, willing to negotiate and reward assistance rather than resort to immediate violence.', 'breton, witch, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally a powerful witch who willingly underwent the hagraven transformation ritual, Melka established herself as the mistress of Blind Cliff Bastion, where she practiced her craft of poison-making and collected curious specimens. She maintained control of her tower until betrayed by Petra, another hagraven who imprisoned her and usurped her domain.', 'Unlike most hagravens, Melka shows a capacity for measured cooperation and honor, keeping her word to reward those who help her. She maintains the typical hagraven fascination with collecting grotesque trophies, particularly eyeballs, and harbors an intense desire for revenge against those who wrong her. Despite her more reasonable nature, she still views humans primarily as ''morsels'' and ''meat'', revealing her inherently predatory perspective.', 'Like all hagravens, Melka appears as a horrific hybrid of woman and crow, with withered, feathered limbs ending in sharp talons. Her hunched form bears the typical features of her kind - wrinkled, grey-skinned face with a hooked beak-like nose, stringy black hair, and unnaturally long fingers with sharp claws.', '* Petra - Bitter rival and usurper who betrayed and imprisoned her * The Last Dragonborn - Potential ally whom she views as a useful ''morsel'' * Other Hagravens - Maintains distance from most of her kind, preferring solitary existence * Former Coven - Likely maintained connections with the witch coven she originated from before transformation', 'Melka serves as the rightful mistress of Blind Cliff Bastion, where she practices poison-making and conducts magical experiments. She maintains and develops the tower''s elaborate trap systems while collecting specimens for her arcane studies.', '* Master of Frost magic, including Ice Spike and Ice Storm spells * Skilled in Restoration magic, particularly Fast Healing and Close Wounds * Expert alchemist specializing in poison creation * Proficient trap maker and mechanical engineer * Knowledge of ritual magic and transformative ceremonies', 'Melka speaks in an unusual, poetic manner with broken syntax, often referring to others as types of meat or food. She frequently repeats words for emphasis and uses peculiar turns of phrase, demonstrating both her non-human nature and possible mental degradation from the hagraven transformation.', '* Reclaim control of Blind Cliff Bastion from Petra * Expand her collection of specimens, particularly eyeballs * Perfect her poison-crafting abilities * Maintain independence from other hagravens while defending her territory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mena', 'Mena is a devoted Breton mother and wife whose life in the mining town of Karthwasten was shattered when her daughter Fjotra was kidnapped by the Forsworn. Her existence is defined by the profound grief and anxiety over her missing child, though she later finds both sorrow and pride in her daughter''s destiny as the Sybil of Dibella.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Mena eventually settled in the Reach with her husband Enmon, choosing the quiet mining town of Karthwasten to raise their family. Their peaceful life was disrupted when their daughter Fjotra was targeted and captured by the Forsworn, later revealed to be the chosen Sybil of Dibella - a discovery that would permanently alter their family''s path.', 'Mena is a deeply emotional and worried mother, often overwhelmed by her circumstances to the point of being unable to fully engage with strangers. She shows signs of depression and anxiety following her daughter''s kidnapping, though she maintains a strong bond with her husband Enmon. Despite her grief, she eventually accepts her daughter''s divine calling with a mixture of maternal pride and lingering sadness.', 'Mena bears the typical features of a Breton woman, with a medium build and average height characteristic of her race. Her face shows signs of worry and stress, with visible aging accelerated by her emotional trauma. Her movements often appear weary and burdened by her emotional state.', '* Enmon - Beloved husband and emotional support system * Fjotra - Cherished daughter who becomes the Sybil of Dibella * Ainethach - Town leader and neighbor in Karthwasten * Forsworn - Antagonistic relationship as her daughter''s kidnappers * Temple of Dibella - Complex relationship as the institution that now cares for her daughter', 'Mena maintains her household in Karthwasten, spending most of her day tending to domestic duties such as sweeping the porch and maintaining their modest home. Her life revolves around these simple tasks, which provide structure during her family''s crisis.', '* Domestic expertise in household management and maintenance * Basic survival skills necessary for life in the Reach * Emotional resilience in facing family tragedy * Adaptation to frontier life in a mining settlement', 'Mena speaks with a heavy emotional weight in her voice, often trailing off or becoming overwhelmed when discussing sensitive topics. Her dialogue is characterized by worry and weariness, frequently deflecting conversations to her husband when she feels unable to continue.', '* Reunite with her daughter Fjotra and ensure her safety * Maintain her family''s stability despite their separation * Accept and support her daughter''s divine calling as Sybil * Find peace with her daughter''s new role while managing her own grief');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mercer_frey', 'Mercer Frey is a cunning and treacherous Breton who rose to become Guildmaster of the Thieves Guild through deception and murder. A former Nightingale who betrayed his oath to Nocturnal, he secretly orchestrated the Guild''s decline while enriching himself through theft and manipulation.', 'breton, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_mercerfrey', '', 'Originally inducted into the Thieves Guild during its prosperous era, Mercer ascended the ranks to become one of the three Nightingales alongside Gallus and Karliah. After stealing the Skeleton Key from the Twilight Sepulcher, he murdered Gallus and framed Karliah for the crime, assuming leadership of the Guild and gradually draining its resources and coffers for his own gain.', 'Mercer is calculating, ruthless, and deeply cynical, viewing loyalty and honor as foolish concepts to be exploited. He maintains a facade of professional leadership while harboring complete disdain for the Guild''s traditional values and its members, whom he sees as tools to be used and discarded.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with sharp, weathered features and calculating eyes. His body is lean and athletic from years of thievery, with numerous old scars from past encounters. His movements are precise and deliberate, reflecting decades of stealth training.', '* Gallus - Former Guildmaster whom he murdered to cover his crimes * Karliah - Fellow Nightingale he betrayed and framed for Gallus''s murder * Brynjolf - Trusted lieutenant within the Guild, though Mercer secretly holds him in contempt * Maven Black-Briar - Powerful business associate who helps maintain the Guild''s presence in Riften * Vald - Personal bodyguard assigned to protect his manor', 'As Guildmaster of the Thieves Guild, Mercer oversees all Guild operations from the Ragged Flagon Cistern while maintaining the appearance of working to restore the organization to its former glory. He secretly uses his position to enrich himself while systematically undermining the Guild''s prosperity.', '* Master-level lockpicking abilities, enhanced by the stolen Skeleton Key * Expert swordsman specializing in quick, lethal strikes * Highly skilled in stealth, infiltration, and escape tactics * Advanced knowledge of Guild operations and criminal networks * Proficient in reading and manipulating people', 'Speaks with calculated authority and thinly veiled condescension, often employing subtle threats and maintaining a cold, professional demeanor. His words are carefully chosen to maintain control while revealing as little as possible about his true intentions.', '* Maintain his power and wealth while keeping his betrayal hidden from the Guild * Protect the Skeleton Key and the source of his enhanced abilities * Eliminate any threats to his position, particularly Karliah * Amass enough wealth to disappear if his crimes are discovered');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('merilar_rendas', 'Merilar Rendas is a brilliant but tragically corrupted Dark Elf sorceress whose groundbreaking research into Solstheim''s albino spiders led to her mental deterioration. Once a promising magical researcher, she now dwells in White Ridge Barrow as a dangerous and deranged figure, consumed by her obsession with spider experimentation and driven to violence by exposure to mysterious magical fumes.', 'darkelf, mage, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Merilar traveled to Solstheim with her brother Servos to conduct magical research, drawn by rumors of unique fauna on the ash-covered island. Their discovery of the albino spiders'' magical receptivity to rubies marked a significant breakthrough, but prolonged exposure to experimental fumes and the intoxicating nature of their power gradually eroded her sanity. The corruption of her mind eventually led her to imprison and leave her own brother to die, marking her complete descent into madness.', 'Once methodical and scholarly, Merilar has become completely unhinged, displaying extreme paranoia and aggressive behavior toward any who approach her domain. She exhibits an obsessive fixation with her spider experiments, showing no remorse for her brother''s death and maintaining delusional justifications for her actions. Her remaining rationality is solely focused on continuing her research, regardless of the cost to herself or others.', 'A Dark Elf woman with the characteristic red eyes and ashen skin of her race, though years of exposure to magical fumes have left her complexion particularly pallid. Her once-graceful features now appear gaunt and twisted, with wild eyes that dart erratically and hands that shake from constant exposure to corrupting magical energies.', '* Servos Rendas - Brother and former research partner whom she imprisoned and left to die * White Ridge Albino Spiders - Treats them as both test subjects and weapons * Local Settlers - Viewed as threats and potential interruptions to her work * College of Winterhold - Likely had previous academic connections before her descent into madness', 'Merilar serves as both researcher and guardian of White Ridge Barrow, continuing her twisted experiments on albino spiders in isolation. Her work, though scientifically significant, has devolved into dangerous and unethical practices that combine spider breeding with destructive magic manipulation.', '* Expert in Alteration magic with focus on creature manipulation * Advanced knowledge of alchemy and magical experimentation * Specialized expertise in spider behavior and magical enhancement * Capable of creating and controlling flame-enchanted spiders * Proficient in defensive magic and magical barriers', 'Her speech patterns are erratic and disjointed, frequently shifting between lucid scientific terminology and maniacal ravings about her experiments. She often talks to herself or her spiders, with her voice alternating between scholarly murmurs and sharp, hostile outbursts.', '* Continue her research into enhancing albino spiders with magical properties * Protect her experimental subjects and research from outside interference * Perfect the process of creating flame-enhanced spiders * Expand her collection of specimens and test subjects');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('michel_lylvieve', 'Michel Lylvieve is a hardworking Breton farmer and devoted family matriarch living in Dragon Bridge, demonstrating the resilient spirit of Skyrim''s common folk. She maintains a delicate balance between managing her household duties and working the land while serving as a cornerstone of Dragon Bridge''s tight-knit farming community.', 'breton, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Michel eventually settled in Dragon Bridge with her husband Azzada, where they established their family farm. Their successful integration into the community and years of agricultural experience have made them respected figures among Dragon Bridge''s residents, particularly known for their generosity in helping neighbors through difficult times.', 'Michel is characterized by her warm, nurturing disposition and strong work ethic, often showing genuine concern for both family and community members. She maintains an optimistic outlook despite Skyrim''s harsh conditions, while displaying practical wisdom in managing household affairs and farm work. Her empathetic nature is evident in her concern for others, such as her worry for Logrolf''s situation in Markarth.', 'Michel possesses the typical Breton features with a sturdy, weather-worn physique developed from years of farm work. Her face shows the natural aging of someone who spends considerable time working outdoors, with subtle smile lines that speak to her friendly disposition.', '* Azzada Lylvieve - Loving husband and farming partner * Clinton Lylvieve - Son whom she helps raise * Julienne Lylvieve - Daughter whom she nurtures and teaches household skills * Logrolf - Old family friend in Markarth she worries about * Dragon Bridge Community - Respected member with good standing among neighbors', 'Michel serves as both a farmer and household manager, dividing her time between agricultural work and domestic duties. Her daily routine involves maintaining the family home, preparing meals, and working the farm fields, demonstrating the typical multiple roles of a farming family matriarch in Skyrim.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Proficient in household management and food preparation * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Skilled in domestic crafts and food preservation techniques', 'Michel speaks in a warm, welcoming manner typical of rural Bretons, using straightforward language colored by agricultural references and domestic concerns. Her tone is caring and maternal, often expressing genuine interest in others'' well-being.', '* Maintain and grow the family farm to ensure her children''s future prosperity * Support her community through difficult times, particularly during the civil war * Protect her family from the increasing dangers in Skyrim * Help old friends like Logrolf when possible');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mikael', 'Mikael is a self-assured Nord bard who performs at the Bannered Mare in Whiterun, known for his persistent romantic pursuits and questionable reputation with women. Despite his often unwanted advances, he maintains a position as a respected entertainer and source of local gossip, having formally studied at the Bards College before his controversial departure.', 'nord, bard, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally trained at the Bards College in Solitude, Mikael was forced to leave due to a scandal involving the headmistress and her husband. He traveled extensively through Cyrodiil building his reputation as a performer before settling in Whiterun, where he authored ''A Gentleman''s Guide to Whiterun'' and established himself as a regular performer at the Bannered Mare.', 'Mikael is overconfident, flirtatious, and often predatory in his pursuit of women, showing little respect for their personal boundaries or relationships status. He maintains an inflated sense of self-importance and charm, frequently boasting about his supposed romantic conquests and musical talents. Despite his problematic behavior, he''s a capable performer and maintains enough social awareness to remain employed and generally tolerated in Whiterun society.', 'A typical Nord male with an athletic build maintained through his active lifestyle as a performer. He carries himself with practiced poise and maintains a well-groomed appearance to support his self-image as a ladies'' man.', '* Carlotta Valentia - Current romantic target who strongly rejects his advances * Hulda - Employer at the Bannered Mare who tolerates his behavior * Various Whiterun women - Subjects of his unwanted attention * Bards College - Former association ended in scandal * Local patrons - Source of income and audience for his performances', 'Professional bard performing regularly at the Bannered Mare inn in Whiterun. He alternates between playing instruments, singing traditional Nordic songs, and interacting with patrons, while also maintaining a side career as an author.', '* Trained musician proficient with multiple instruments including the lute * Accomplished vocalist specializing in Nordic ballads and tavern songs * Skilled writer and author * Practiced in the art of persuasion and charm, albeit often unsuccessful * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger', 'Speaks with an affected charm and deliberately sophisticated manner, often employing suggestive undertones and boastful rhetoric. His vocabulary alternates between poetic flourishes when performing and more direct, sometimes crude approaches in his attempts at romantic conquest.', '* Pursue and eventually win over Carlotta Valentia despite her clear lack of interest * Build a greater reputation as a renowned bard throughout Skyrim * Expand his influence and romantic conquests in Whiterun * Publish more works following his ''Gentleman''s Guide to Whiterun''');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mikrul_gauldurson', 'Mikrul Gauldurson is the youngest of three brothers who murdered their father Gauldur and stole his powerful amulet, becoming consumed by its corrupting influence. A powerful Nord mage driven to madness, he terrorized villages across Skyrim until being defeated and sealed away in Folgunthur by Archmage Geirmund''s forces after a legendary three-day battle.', 'nord', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born into the prestigious Gauldurson family, Mikrul was the youngest son of the renowned mage Gauldur. Together with his brothers, he murdered his father out of jealousy and greed, dividing Gauldur''s powerful amulet between them. The amulet''s power drove him to madness, leading him on a rampage through Skyrim''s villages until he was finally defeated and entombed in Folgunthur.', 'Aggressive and power-hungry, Mikrul embodies the corruption that overtook him after claiming his portion of his father''s amulet. His mental state deteriorated into paranoid madness, making him extremely territorial and violent. Despite his insanity, he maintains enough cunning to be a dangerous opponent, particularly in magical combat.', 'A tall, imposing Nord with the gaunt features typical of ancient Nordic mages. His physical form has been preserved by the magical nature of his undeath, though his flesh has the grey pallor characteristic of the draugr. His eyes glow with an unnatural blue light, reflecting the magical energies that sustain him.', '* Gauldur - Father whom he murdered out of greed and jealousy * Jyrik Gauldurson - Elder brother and fellow conspirator in their father''s murder * Sigdis Gauldurson - Middle brother who shared in their treachery * Archmage Geirmund - Mortal enemy who defeated and entombed him * High King Harald - Ruler who ordered the destruction of all records of the Gauldursons'' treachery', 'Once a respected mage in his own right, Mikrul became a feared magical terrorist after his corruption by the amulet''s power. In undeath, he serves as an eternal guardian of his portion of Gauldur''s amulet, bound to Folgunthur by powerful magic.', '* Master-level Destruction magic specializing in frost spells * Powerful necromancer capable of raising and controlling the dead * Enhanced magical abilities granted by his fragment of Gauldur''s amulet * Skilled in ancient Nordic magic and rituals * Exceptional magical resistance and regeneration abilities', 'Speaks with an aggressive, hostile tone filled with ancient Nordic expressions and threats. His voice carries the hollow, ethereal quality characteristic of powerful draugr, enhanced by magical resonance.', '* Protect his fragment of Gauldur''s amulet at any cost * Maintain his eternal vigil over Folgunthur * Destroy any who dare to enter his domain * Preserve the power he gained through patricide');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('millius', 'Millius was a scholarly Imperial assistant who worked alongside Gratian Caerellius exploring the ancient ruins within Raven Rock Mine. Known for his cautious approach and archaeological expertise, he met a tragic end while trying to protect his mentor from the consequences of disturbing an ancient artifact.', 'imperial, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Millius likely received formal education in archaeology and ancient Nordic history before traveling to Solstheim to assist in excavation projects. He was specifically recruited by Gratian Caerellius for his expertise in Nordic ruins and demonstrated exceptional skill in translating ancient texts and identifying historical artifacts.', 'Millius was characterized by his prudent and methodical approach to archaeological work, often serving as a voice of reason to temper his mentor''s enthusiasm. Though naturally cautious, he displayed remarkable courage when faced with danger, choosing to stand and fight alongside Gratian rather than flee when their discovery awakened the draugr.', 'As an Imperial scholar, Millius likely possessed the typical features of his race - light skin, dark hair, and strong facial features common to Cyrodilic peoples. His years of archaeological work would have given him a sturdy build despite his academic background, with callused hands from excavation work.', '* Gratian Caerellius - Mentor and superior whom he served as research assistant * East Empire Company - Employer who funded their archaeological expeditions * Raven Rock Settlers - Professional acquaintances within the mining community * Fellow Scholars - Maintained correspondence with other Imperial researchers', 'Millius served as a research assistant and archaeological expert for Gratian Caerellius, working under the East Empire Company''s authority. His duties included documenting findings, translating ancient texts, and providing scholarly insight into Nordic ruins and artifacts.', '* Expertise in Nordic archaeology and ancient artifact identification * Proficient in translating ancient Nordic texts and inscriptions * Basic combat training for self-defense in dangerous ruins * Knowledge of preservation techniques for historical artifacts * Experience in careful excavation methods', 'Millius spoke with the educated diction of an Imperial scholar, using precise terminology when discussing archaeological matters. His tone was typically measured and diplomatic, especially when voicing concerns about potentially dangerous discoveries.', '* Advance the understanding of ancient Nordic culture through careful study and documentation * Protect important historical sites and artifacts from damage or misuse * Build a respected reputation in the field of archaeology * Ensure safe and responsible excavation practices in Raven Rock Mine');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('milore_ienth', 'Milore Ienth is a skilled Dark Elf apothecary who plays a vital role in Raven Rock''s survival through her expert alchemical knowledge and training capabilities. Together with her farmer husband, she helps sustain the settlement by providing essential potions and ingredients while also serving as one of the few expert-level alchemy trainers on Solstheim.', 'darkelf, alchemist, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Milore and her husband fled following the Red Mountain''s eruption, eventually settling in Morthal, Skyrim. There, she studied under Lami, the town''s alchemist, developing her expertise over several years before relocating to Raven Rock on Solstheim, where she and her husband established themselves as crucial contributors to the settlement''s survival.', 'Milore is a diligent and hardworking individual with a strong sense of community responsibility. She maintains a practical, business-minded approach to her work while showing genuine concern for Raven Rock''s wellbeing. Her dedication to alchemy and teaching demonstrates both patience and wisdom, traits that have earned her respect among the townspeople.', 'Like most Dunmer, Milore has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of her race. She bears the angular features common to Dark Elves, with a lean build typical of those who spend long hours working with alchemical equipment and tending to plants.', '* Garyn Ienth - Beloved husband and farming partner who supplies many of her ingredients * Lami - Former alchemy mentor from Morthal * Raven Rock Residents - Respected community member and essential service provider * Students - Various apprentices seeking expert-level alchemy training', 'Milore serves as Raven Rock''s primary alchemist, creating and selling potions while offering expert-level training in alchemy. She manages her own alchemy shop and works in tandem with her husband''s farming operation to provide essential services to the settlement.', '* Expert-level knowledge of alchemy and ingredient properties * Advanced understanding of farming and ingredient cultivation * Skilled at potion brewing and ingredient identification * Capable teacher with extensive knowledge of alchemical theory * Basic self-defense abilities with a steel dagger', 'Milore speaks in a professional yet approachable manner, using terminology common to merchants and alchemists. Her speech reflects her Dunmer heritage and education, with clear diction and occasional use of specialized alchemical terms.', '* Maintain a stable supply of potions and ingredients for Raven Rock''s survival * Continue developing her alchemical knowledge and techniques * Pass on her expertise to the next generation of alchemists * Support her husband in keeping their farm productive despite Solstheim''s harsh conditions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('miraak', 'Miraak stands as the first Dragonborn in history, a former Dragon Priest whose ambition and thirst for power led him to betray his dragon masters and align with the Daedric Prince Hermaeus Mora. His mastery of both the Thu''um and forbidden knowledge makes him one of the most formidable beings in Tamriel''s history, with abilities far beyond those of ordinary mortals.', 'nord, solstheim, dragon, daedric', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born in the Merethic Era as a Proto-Nord, Miraak rose to become one of the most powerful Dragon Priests, serving the dragons who ruled over Solstheim. After discovering his Dragonborn nature, he sought out forbidden knowledge from Hermaeus Mora, eventually betraying the dragons and establishing his own kingdom. Following his defeat by Vahlok the Jailor, he retreated to Apocrypha, spending thousands of years amassing knowledge and power before attempting to return to Tamriel in 4E 201.', 'Miraak embodies supreme arrogance and an unshakeable belief in his own superiority, viewing even other Dragonborn as inferior beings. His millennia of isolation in Apocrypha have only reinforced his megalomania and detachment from humanity, while his endless pursuit of power reveals a deeply ambitious and patient character willing to wait centuries to achieve his goals. His betrayal of both the dragons and Hermaeus Mora demonstrates his ultimate loyalty only to himself.', 'Miraak is a tall, powerfully built Nord male with the imposing physique typical of ancient Dragon Priests. His true face is rarely seen, but his physical form has been enhanced and possibly altered by his long exposure to Hermaeus Mora''s realm, giving him an otherworldly presence that transcends his mortal origins.', '* Hermaeus Mora - Former master and patron Daedric Prince, later betrayed * Vahlok the Jailor - Ancient rival who defeated him in combat * Dragons - Former masters whom he betrayed and enslaved * Last Dragonborn - Rival and potential usurper of his power * Cultists - Fanatical followers who worship him as a god', 'Miraak originally served as a Dragon Priest, one of the highest positions in ancient Nordic society. After his betrayal, he became both a self-proclaimed ruler of Solstheim and a champion of Hermaeus Mora, though his true occupation during his time in Apocrypha was that of a seeker of forbidden knowledge and power.', '* Master of the Thu''um with unique Shouts including Bend Will * Powerful magic user with access to forbidden knowledge from Apocrypha * Ability to absorb dragon souls and dominate dragons * Expert in both magical and physical combat * Profound understanding of ancient Nordic and Daedric magic', 'Miraak speaks with supreme confidence and condescension, using archaic language that reflects his ancient origins. His words carry power and authority, often dismissing others with contempt while emphasizing his own superiority and firstborn status as Dragonborn.', '* Return to Tamriel and reclaim his dominion over Solstheim * Eliminate the Last Dragonborn to prove his superiority * Accumulate enough power to break free from Hermaeus Mora''s influence * Establish himself as the supreme Dragonborn ruler of Tamriel');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mirabelle_ervine', 'Mirabelle Ervine serves as the Master Wizard of the College of Winterhold, acting as second-in-command to Arch-Mage Savos Aren and managing the institution''s daily operations. She is a powerful Breton mage who combines administrative efficiency with magical expertise, serving as both a stern gatekeeper and protective figure for the College community.', 'breton, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_mirabelleervine', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Mirabelle demonstrated exceptional magical aptitude from an early age and pursued advanced studies in various schools of magic. She rose through the ranks at the College of Winterhold through her combination of magical prowess and administrative capability, eventually earning the trust of Savos Aren who appointed her as Master Wizard.', 'Mirabelle is stern, pragmatic, and fiercely protective of the College''s interests and reputation. She maintains a professional demeanor that can come across as cold or dismissive to outsiders, but shows genuine concern for the well-being of students and faculty. Her calculating nature and sharp intellect make her an excellent administrator, though she often struggles with the political aspects of maintaining the College''s reputation in Skyrim.', 'Mirabelle is a middle-aged Breton woman with sharp features and an commanding presence. She maintains excellent posture and carries herself with dignity befitting her station. Her face shows signs of aging from years of magical study and exposure to Winterhold''s harsh climate.', '* Savos Aren - Direct superior and trusted colleague * Sergius Turrianus - Close colleague with whom she regularly dines * Faralda - Trusted colleague who assists in screening new applicants * Ancano - Distrusted Thalmor advisor whom she keeps under careful observation * Citizens of Winterhold - Tense relationship due to historical mistrust of the College', 'As Master Wizard, Mirabelle oversees the College''s daily operations, including student admission, faculty management, and facility maintenance. She serves as the primary administrator and second-in-command, handling everything from security concerns to supply logistics while reporting directly to the Arch-Mage.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly fire-based spells * Accomplished practitioner of Alteration magic, including protective spells * Skilled in Restoration magic for healing and warding * Advanced theoretical knowledge of all schools of magic * Exceptional administrative and organizational abilities * Proficient in magical research and documentation', 'Mirabelle speaks in a formal, educated manner with carefully chosen words and precise diction. Her tone is often clipped and businesslike, though it can warm slightly when addressing trusted colleagues.', '* Maintain the College''s standards of magical education while preserving its independence * Protect the College''s reputation and interests in an increasingly hostile Skyrim * Expand the College''s influence and resources without compromising its integrity * Investigate and neutralize potential threats to the College''s security');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mirmulnir', 'Mirmulnir is an ancient and formidable dragon who survived the Dragon War without being slain, choosing to hide rather than face extinction. As one of the few dragons who was never actually killed and resurrected by Alduin, he represents a direct link to the original dragon hierarchy of the Merethic Era.', 'dragon', '', '', 'sk_dragon', '', 'Unlike many other dragons who were slain during the Dragon War and later resurrected by Alduin, Mirmulnir managed to survive by going into hiding for thousands of years. The Atlas of Dragons specifically lists him as ''Known to Live,'' suggesting he maintained a low profile until Alduin''s return, when he emerged to once again serve his master. His survival through the ages implies exceptional cunning and adaptability uncommon among his kind.', 'Mirmulnir exhibits the typical pride and arrogance common to dragons, viewing mortals as inferior beings worthy only of domination. Despite his long period of hiding, he maintains an aggressive and confrontational nature, eagerly engaging in combat when discovered. His decision to survive through stealth rather than face death suggests a pragmatic streak unusual among dragons.', 'A massive, scaled dragon whose exact coloration and features vary depending on the power level at which he manifests. His physical form embodies the might and majesty typical of his species, with powerful wings, razor-sharp claws, and horned head characteristic of the dov.', '* Alduin - Master and superior whom he serves loyally * Other Dragons - Fellow dov who share his desire for dominance over mortals * Whiterun Guards - Viewed as prey and inferior beings * Dovahkiin - Recognized nemesis and ultimate slayer', 'As a dragon, Mirmulnir serves as one of Alduin''s lieutenants in the effort to reestablish dragon dominion over Skyrim. His role involves terrorizing mortal settlements and asserting draconic supremacy through force.', '* Powerful Thu''um (Dragon Shouts) including fire breath * Exceptional flight capabilities and aerial combat expertise * Superior physical strength and natural armor * Tactical intelligence that enabled centuries of survival * Ability to adapt combat style based on circumstances', 'Speaks in the typical dragon manner, using a deep, intimidating voice and occasionally mixing Dovahzul (dragon language) with common speech. His dialogue reflects both his ancient nature and his contempt for mortals, often taunting opponents during battle.', '* Serve Alduin in reestablishing dragon dominion over mortals * Assert his power and superiority through combat and conquest * Maintain his position in the draconic hierarchy * Eliminate threats to dragon rule, particularly the Dovahkiin');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mirri_severin', 'Mirri Severin presents herself as the daughter of a wealthy Dark Elf family in Raven Rock, but harbors dark secrets about her true identity and relationship with her supposed father. She maintains a carefully crafted public persona of a flirtatious noble while participating in a decade-long deception that threatens the town''s leadership.', 'darkelf, noble, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Arriving in Raven Rock approximately ten years ago, Mirri established herself as part of the wealthy Severin family, though this is revealed to be an elaborate facade. She and Vendil Severin are actually lovers posing as father and daughter, participating in a long-term plot against Councilor Morvayn. Their true origins and motivations remain carefully hidden behind their manufactured identity as respected community members.', 'Mirri exhibits a duplicitous nature, presenting herself as a bored, flirtatious noble''s daughter while concealing her true cunning and ambition. She shows disdain for the common people of Raven Rock and frequently expresses boredom with her surroundings, using her seductive personality as a tool to maintain her cover. Despite her act, she demonstrates ruthless dedication to their long-term scheme.', 'Mirri possesses the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of a Dunmer, with sharp, attractive features that aid her flirtatious persona. She carries herself with the practiced grace of nobility, though her movements suggest combat training beneath her refined exterior. Her body language often conveys both sensuality and carefully controlled tension.', '* Vendil Severin - Lover and co-conspirator posing as her father * Tilisu Severin - Fellow conspirator who poses as her mother, shows jealousy over Mirri''s relationship with Vendil * Councilor Morvayn - Target of their family''s secret plot * Raven Rock Citizens - Maintains superficial relationships while privately viewing them with contempt', 'Mirri maintains the appearance of a wealthy noble''s daughter while secretly working as part of a conspiracy against Raven Rock''s leadership. Her daily routine of shopping, drinking, and socializing serves as cover for more nefarious activities.', '* Skilled in deception and maintaining false identities * Proficient with daggers and likely trained in combat * Expert in manipulation and seduction techniques * Adept at gathering information through social interactions', 'Mirri speaks in a sultry, flirtatious manner with male characters while maintaining an air of noble superiority. Her speech patterns shift between seductive charm and barely concealed disdain, depending on her audience.', '* Complete the decade-long plot against Councilor Morvayn * Escape the monotony of life in Raven Rock once their mission is complete * Maintain her cover identity until their plans come to fruition * Continue her relationship with Vendil while keeping their true connection hidden');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mjoll_the_lioness', 'Mjoll the Lioness is a fierce Nord warrior and former adventurer who found purpose in protecting the citizens of Riften after a near-death experience in a Dwemer ruin. Despite her adventuring days being behind her, she maintains a strong moral compass and actively works to combat the corruption plaguing her adopted home, particularly focusing her efforts against the Thieves Guild''s influence.', 'nord, warrior, rift, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born to a family of Nordic warriors, Mjoll spent her early years traveling Tamriel as an adventurer, delving into dangerous ruins and fighting fearsome creatures. Her promising career was cut short when she nearly died exploring a Dwemer ruin, where she lost her prized sword Grimsever and was saved by an Imperial named Aerin. This life-changing experience led her to settle in Riften, where she witnessed the city''s decay under criminal influence.', 'Mjoll exhibits a strong sense of justice and unwavering moral principles, often speaking openly against corruption despite potential dangers. She is fiercely loyal to those she considers friends and demonstrates a protective nature towards the common people of Riften. Though she yearns for her adventuring days, she has found new purpose in civic duty and shows remarkable patience in her quest to reform Riften.', 'Mjoll is a tall, muscular Nord woman with the battle-hardened physique of a seasoned warrior. Her face bears several small scars from her adventures, and she moves with the confident stride of someone well-versed in combat. Her strong Nordic features are complemented by war paint that accentuates her fierce appearance.', '* Aerin - Close friend and savior who rescued her from death, now her constant companion * Maven Black-Briar - Antagonistic relationship due to Maven''s corrupt influence over Riften * Thieves Guild - Sworn enemies whom she actively works against * Citizens of Riften - Protective relationship as their self-appointed guardian * The Jarl - Respectful but frustrated relationship due to the Jarl''s perceived inaction against corruption', 'Mjoll serves as a self-appointed protector of Riften''s citizens, working to expose corruption and criminal activities within the city. She frequently patrols the streets, offering advice and protection to those in need, while gathering information about the Thieves Guild''s operations.', '* Master-level proficiency with two-handed weapons, particularly greatswords * Exceptional knowledge of Dwemer ruins and artifacts * Advanced heavy armor combat techniques * Survival skills honed through years of adventuring * Natural leadership abilities and tactical combat expertise', 'Mjoll speaks with a strong Nordic accent and maintains a formal, almost theatrical manner of speech that reflects her adventuring background. She often peppers her conversation with tales of her past exploits and speaks passionately when discussing Riften''s problems.', '* Rid Riften of the Thieves Guild''s influence and restore the city to its former glory * Recover her lost sword Grimsever to reclaim a piece of her adventuring past * Inspire others to stand up against corruption and injustice * Eventually return to exploration of Dwemer ruins, but only after ensuring Riften''s safety');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('modhna', 'Modhna is a reclusive Breton vampire who serves as a low-ranking member of Lord Harkon''s court at Volkihar Keep. She represents the more feral and self-serving aspects of vampire society, caring little for politics or social connections while focusing primarily on feeding and survival.', 'breton, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_femalevampire', '', 'Originally a Breton warrior before her turning, Modhna likely joined Harkon''s court seeking the power and sustenance that Volkihar Keep provides. Her transition from mortal to vampire appears to have intensified her antisocial tendencies, leading her to embrace a solitary existence focused purely on feeding and serving the basic requirements of court life.', 'Modhna exhibits a distinctly antisocial and dismissive personality, showing little interest in anything beyond satisfying her hunger and maintaining her position in the court. She is territorial about her feeding rights and demonstrates no ambition for political advancement or social connections. Her responses to others are consistently brusque and impatient, suggesting a deep-seated misanthropy that may predate her vampirism.', 'As a Breton vampire, Modhna possesses the characteristic pale skin and glowing eyes common to her kind. Her features likely retain the typical Breton traits of a somewhat slight build and medium height, though transformed by the gaunt, predatory aspects of vampirism.', '* Lord Harkon - Serves him out of necessity rather than loyalty * Fellow Volkihar Vampires - Maintains minimal required interaction * Human Cattle - Views them purely as food sources * Other Court Members - Shows clear preference for avoiding social contact', 'Modhna serves as a low-ranking member of the Volkihar vampire court, primarily focusing on feeding and maintaining the minimum expected presence at court. Her duties likely include defending the keep when needed, though she shows no interest in advancing her position or taking on additional responsibilities.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat from her warrior background * Vampire abilities including enhanced strength and supernatural powers * Survival skills focused on feeding and self-preservation * Basic court etiquette, though rarely employed', 'Modhna speaks in short, dismissive statements that often end conversations before they begin. Her tone is consistently cold and impatient, with no attempt to mask her desire for solitude.', '* Maintain access to feeding opportunities within Volkihar Keep * Avoid unnecessary social interaction or court politics * Preserve her position in the court while expending minimal effort * Protect her claimed feeding territories from other vampires');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mogdurz', 'Mogdurz is a dedicated Orc miner at Gloombound Mine who embodies the Orcish values of hard work, discipline, and devotion to Malacath. She serves as both a spiritual adherent and physical laborer, believing that the extraction of precious ores strengthens the Orcish people and honors their Daedric patron.', 'orc, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in the stronghold of Narzulbur, Mogdurz learned the art of mining from an early age as part of her cultural heritage. She has spent decades honing her craft in Gloombound Mine, becoming one of the most experienced miners of ebony ore in Skyrim. Her unwavering dedication to Malacath''s teachings has earned her respect among her fellow Orcs, though she remains relatively isolated from the wider world beyond the mine.', 'Mogdurz is stoic, pragmatic, and deeply religious, viewing her daily labor as a form of worship to Malacath. She has little patience for idle conversation or outside interference, preferring to focus entirely on her work. Her harsh exterior masks a deep sense of pride in her cultural heritage and a genuine belief that her work contributes to the strength of all Orsimer.', 'Mogdurz has the typical robust build of an Orc female, with prominent tusks and thick, calloused hands from years of mining work. Her green-tinted skin bears numerous scars and calluses from mining accidents, while her muscular frame reflects the physical demands of her profession.', '* Chief Mauhulakh - Stronghold leader whom she respects and serves * Fellow Miners - Professional but distant working relationships * Dushnamub - Fellow miner who shares her devotion to work * Malacath - Spiritual connection as a devoted follower', 'Mogdurz serves as a senior miner in Gloombound Mine, specializing in the extraction of valuable ebony ore. Her position involves both physical labor and maintaining the spiritual connection between the mining work and Malacath''s teachings, making her role both practical and religious in nature.', '* Expert in ebony and iron ore extraction techniques * Proficient with mining tools and equipment maintenance * Skilled in identifying valuable ore veins * Basic combat abilities with war axe for self-defense * Knowledge of traditional Orcish mining practices and rituals', 'Her speech is blunt and terse, with a thick Orcish accent and frequent references to Malacath. She uses minimal words to convey maximum meaning, often speaking in short, declarative sentences that reflect her no-nonsense attitude.', '* Continue honoring Malacath through dedicated mining work * Maintain the productivity and spiritual significance of Gloombound Mine * Pass on traditional Orcish mining knowledge to younger generations * Strengthen the Orcish people through the fruits of her labor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mogrul', 'Mogrul is a scholarly Orc mage who has dedicated his life to the study of alchemy and magic in the remote town of Dagon Fel. As the town''s resident alchemist and Mages Guild representative, he serves as both a merchant of magical goods and a respected source of arcane knowledge for the local community.', 'orc, mage, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born to a small Orsimer settlement in Morrowind, Mogrul showed an unusual aptitude for magic from an early age, breaking from the warrior traditions of his people. He pursued formal magical education at the Mages Guild in Vivec City before establishing himself in Dagon Fel, where he has spent decades honing his alchemical expertise and building a reputation as a reliable source of magical knowledge and supplies.', 'Patient and methodical in his approach to both magic and social interactions, Mogrul defies the stereotype of the aggressive Orc warrior. He maintains a calm, scholarly demeanor and takes genuine pleasure in sharing his knowledge with others, though he can become stern when dealing with those who show disrespect for magical arts. His dedication to precision in alchemy has made him somewhat perfectionist in nature.', 'Mogrul is a tall, well-built Orc with the characteristic green skin and tusks of his race, though his features are somewhat softer than typical Orsimer. His hands show the careful precision of an alchemist, with slight staining from years of working with various ingredients. Despite his scholarly pursuits, he maintains the muscular physique common to his people.', '* Mages Guild - Respected member and local representative * Local Traders - Maintains professional relationships for acquiring rare ingredients * Town Residents - Generally well-regarded by the community * Traveling Merchants - Regular contacts for exotic alchemical components * Apprentice Mages - Occasional mentor to those seeking alchemical knowledge', 'As the resident alchemist and Mages Guild representative in Dagon Fel, Mogrul maintains a shop selling potions, ingredients, and magical supplies. He also serves as an unofficial advisor on magical matters to the town''s leadership and provides alchemical services to those in need.', '* Master-level knowledge of alchemy and potion-making * Proficient in Restoration and Alteration schools of magic * Expert understanding of magical theory and enchanting principles * Skilled herbalist with extensive knowledge of ingredient properties * Accomplished researcher with focus on magical phenomena', 'Mogrul speaks in a measured, articulate manner that reflects his academic background, often using technical terminology when discussing alchemy or magic. His voice carries the gravelly quality typical of Orcs, but his tone remains gentle and patient, especially when explaining complex concepts.', '* Advance the understanding of alchemical principles through research and experimentation * Establish a formal school of alchemy in Dagon Fel * Document and preserve traditional Dunmer alchemical practices * Bridge the gap between traditional Orcish medicine and modern alchemy * Expand the influence of the Mages Guild in outlying settlements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('moira', 'Moira is a delusional and obsessive hagraven residing in Witchmist Grove who believes she is romantically involved with the Dragonborn following their drunken escapades. Despite her initial non-hostile demeanor, she harbors intense jealousy and possessiveness over her supposed betrothed, revealing the darker aspects of her transformed nature.', 'breton, witch, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalevampire', '', 'Once a human witch who willingly underwent the horrific transformation ritual to become a hagraven, Moira sacrificed her humanity for power and immortality. Her isolation in Witchmist Grove and practice of dark magic have gradually eroded her grip on reality, leading to increasingly unstable behavior and desperate longing for companionship.', 'Moira exhibits extreme possessiveness and romantic delusions, coupled with rapid mood swings between affection and violent jealousy. Her mental state reflects the typical degradation seen in hagravens, where human emotions become twisted and intensified by their transformation, resulting in obsessive behavior and inability to process rejection.', 'Like all hagravens, Moira possesses a grotesque hybrid form combining features of both human and avian anatomy. Her body is emaciated and hunched, with long, gnarled fingers ending in sharp talons, while her face bears the characteristic beak-like nose and feathered elements typical of her kind.', '* Esmerelda - Perceived rival in love, possibly another hagraven * Ysolda - Indirect connection through the Dragonborn''s quest * The Dragonborn - Object of obsessive affection and delusional romance * Other Hagravens - Loose association through shared nature, though largely solitary', 'Moira serves as a witch and practitioner of dark magic, maintaining her territory at Witchmist Grove. She likely engages in typical hagraven activities such as creating magical artifacts and performing dark rituals, though her obsession with romance appears to have overtaken most other pursuits.', '* Proficient in destruction magic and curse-casting * Skilled in alchemy and creation of magical artifacts * Natural ability to command and control birds * Expertise in dark transformation rituals and blood magic', 'Moira speaks with dramatic flair and intense emotion, often using endearments and passionate declarations. Her speech patterns alternate between loving devotion and jealous accusations, reflecting her unstable mental state.', '* Consummate her perceived marriage with the Dragonborn * Prevent any rivals from stealing her ''beloved'' * Maintain possession of the wedding ring at all costs * Preserve her territory at Witchmist Grove');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('molgrom_twice-killed', 'Molgrom Twice-Killed is a rebellious former Thieves Guild member whose pride and violent methods led to his imprisonment in Riften Jail. A Nord thief who earned his self-styled moniker after surviving a near-fatal stabbing at the Ragged Flagon, he represents the more aggressive and uncontrolled element that the Guild typically tries to avoid.', 'nord, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally a standard member of the Thieves Guild, Molgrom gained notoriety after surviving a violent confrontation at the Ragged Flagon where he was stabbed but saved by Vex. His methods grew increasingly violent over time, leading to confrontations with Guild leadership, particularly Brynjolf, who eventually arranged his imprisonment through Maven Black-Briar''s connections.', 'Proud, confrontational, and unapologetically violent, Molgrom believes that the ends justify the means in pursuit of profit. He harbors deep resentment toward authority figures, particularly Brynjolf, and shows a stubborn refusal to adapt his methods to the Guild''s more subtle approach. Despite his aggressive nature, he shows a softer side in his friendship with Vex.', 'A rugged Nord male with the weathered features typical of a career criminal. His body likely bears various scars from his violent encounters, particularly a prominent stab wound from his near-death experience at the Ragged Flagon.', '* Brynjolf - Antagonistic relationship with his former Guild superior who arranged his imprisonment * Vex - Close friend and savior who prevented his death at the Ragged Flagon * Maven Black-Briar - Indirect adversary who facilitated his imprisonment through her connections * Thieves Guild - Former associates whom he views with mixed contempt and longing * Riften Guards - Current jailers who keep him imprisoned on the Guild''s behalf', 'Currently an imprisoned former thief serving time in Riften Jail. Before his incarceration, he was an active member of the Thieves Guild who specialized in more aggressive forms of acquisition, often involving violence and intimidation.', '* Proficient in aggressive theft techniques and intimidation * Experienced in close combat and knife fighting * Survival skills demonstrated by living through normally fatal wounds * Basic understanding of Guild techniques and operations * Street-smart with knowledge of Riften''s criminal underground', 'Speaks in a rough, informal manner with frequent use of sarcasm and profanity. His dialogue is often dismissive and confrontational, reflecting his bitter attitude toward his current situation.', '* Secure release from Riften Jail and return to his criminal activities * Prove his methods superior to Brynjolf''s more cautious approach * Potentially seek revenge against those who imprisoned him * Regain his position in Riften''s criminal underworld, either within or outside the Guild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('moric_sidrey', 'Moric Sidrey is a scholarly Vigilant of Stendarr who led the excavation efforts at Ruunvald, ultimately falling under the enchanting influence of the mysterious entity Minorne. His tragic transformation from a dedicated demon hunter to an enchanted follower demonstrates the dangerous allure of the very forces the Vigilants seek to combat.', 'breton, mage, rift, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born into a scholarly Breton family with a long history of service to the Vigilants of Stendarr, Moric received extensive education in both magical arts and religious doctrine. His exceptional intellect and dedication to understanding supernatural threats led to his rapid rise within the Vigilant ranks, eventually earning him leadership of the Ruunvald expedition. His academic approach to hunting Daedra and supernatural entities set him apart from his more militant peers.', 'Moric exhibits a careful, analytical mindset typical of scholarly Bretons, preferring to study and understand supernatural threats rather than rushing to confront them. His intellectual curiosity occasionally overshadows his caution, as evidenced by his fascination with Minorne. Despite his religious devotion, he harbors a romantic streak that makes him susceptible to supernatural manipulation.', 'Moric is a middle-aged Breton of average height with the typical slight build common to his race. His scholarly lifestyle is reflected in his pale complexion and slight stoop from long hours of study and writing. His face bears the weathered features of someone who spends time both in study and in the field.', '* Minorne - Object of enchanted devotion and fascination * Vigilants of Stendarr - Former brothers and sisters in arms * Florentius Baenius - Fellow Vigilant who may have warned against the excavation * Excavation Team - Led and worked alongside them before their collective enchantment', 'As a senior Vigilant of Stendarr, Moric serves as both a religious warrior-priest and scholar specializing in supernatural threats. His role as expedition leader at Ruunvald combines his archaeological interests with his duties as a Vigilant, though his leadership ultimately leads to tragedy.', '* Advanced practitioner of Restoration magic, particularly protective and healing spells * Skilled in Alteration magic for defensive purposes * Accomplished scholar and researcher with extensive knowledge of Daedra and supernatural entities * Capable writer and record keeper as evidenced by his journals and scripture * Basic mining and excavation expertise gained during the Ruunvald project', 'Moric speaks with the refined vocabulary of a scholar, often incorporating religious terminology and academic references. His writing style is particularly eloquent, especially when describing Minorne, revealing both his education and romantic nature.', '* Uncover the secrets buried within Ruunvald * Document and study supernatural phenomena for the benefit of the Vigilants * Serve Stendarr through the elimination of Daedric influences * Spread the worship and devotion to Minorne (after enchantment)');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('morven', 'Morven is a seemingly humble Breton servant in Markarth who secretly operates as a devoted Forsworn agent and personal bodyguard to Nepos the Nose. His unassuming position as a house servant provides the perfect cover for his true role in the Forsworn''s clandestine operations within the city.', 'breton, peasant, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born among the Forsworn in the Reach, Morven was carefully selected and trained to serve as an undercover operative within Markarth''s walls. His natural ability to blend in and appear non-threatening made him an ideal choice for infiltrating Nepos''s household, where he has served faithfully for several years while maintaining his cover as a simple servant.', 'Morven is exceptionally disciplined and devoted to both his cover identity and the Forsworn cause, demonstrated by his tireless work ethic and ability to maintain his facade without breaks. He exhibits unwavering loyalty to Nepos and the Forsworn movement, willing to sacrifice his life to protect their secrets. Despite his menial role, he maintains constant vigilance and shows remarkable patience in executing his long-term mission.', 'Morven possesses the typical Breton features with a medium build that allows him to appear unthreatening while maintaining the physical capability needed for his true role. His years of domestic service have given him callused hands and a slightly stooped posture that helps sell his servant disguise.', '* Nepos the Nose - Employer and superior in the Forsworn hierarchy whom he''s sworn to protect * Uaile - Fellow undercover Forsworn agent in Nepos''s house * Tynan - Colleague in maintaining Nepos''s household and Forsworn operations * Forsworn Movement - Deeply committed member of the organization * Markarth Guard - Maintains cautious distance while avoiding suspicion', 'Officially, Morven serves as a house servant in Nepos''s residence, maintaining the appearance of a dedicated domestic worker. Covertly, he operates as a Forsworn agent and personal bodyguard to Nepos the Nose, ready to eliminate any threats to their operation.', '* Proficient in stealth and maintaining cover identities * Skilled with daggers and close-quarters combat * Expert in domestic services as part of his cover * Trained in witchblade magic combining spellcasting with melee combat * Knowledgeable in Forsworn customs and operations', 'Morven speaks in short, deferential phrases befitting a servant, carefully measuring his words to avoid revealing his true nature. He maintains a humble, slightly submissive tone when dealing with visitors while being direct and firm when his cover is blown.', '* Protect Nepos the Nose and maintain the security of Forsworn operations in Markarth * Support the Forsworn''s ultimate goal of reclaiming the Reach * Maintain his cover identity until it no longer serves the Forsworn cause * Eliminate any threats to the Forsworn''s presence in Markarth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('morven_stroud', 'Morven Stroud is a formerly successful Breton merchant whose fateful transaction with necromancers led to his soul being trapped in the Soul Cairn. Despite his unfortunate circumstances, he maintains his merchant''s spirit and entrepreneurial mindset, establishing himself as one of the few ''traders'' in the Soul Cairn dealing in soul husks.', 'breton, merchant', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Morven built a reputation as one of the region''s most sought-after traders, with customers tracking him down specifically for his wares. His prosperous career came to an abrupt end when he unknowingly sold counterfeit ingredients to a coven of necromancers, who responded by killing him and trapping his soul. He arrived in the Soul Cairn with his horse, wagon, and remaining merchandise intact.', 'Despite his grim circumstances, Morven maintains a sardonic sense of humor and a surprisingly upbeat demeanor. He demonstrates remarkable adaptability by continuing his trader''s lifestyle even in death, showing both resourcefulness and resilience. While generally friendly, he exhibits traces of bitterness about his fate and occasionally makes cynical remarks about his past life.', 'As a soul in the Soul Cairn, Morven appears as a translucent, ethereal figure with the typical Breton features - a medium build and average height characteristic of his race. His form maintains the general appearance he had in life, though with the ghostly blue luminescence common to all Soul Cairn inhabitants.', '* Necromancer Coven - His murderers who trapped his soul after he sold them fake ingredients * Fellow Soul Cairn Inhabitants - Maintains casual trading relationships with other trapped souls * Living Traders - Former professional network from his days in High Rock, now lost to him * Ideal Master - Indirect overlords of his current existence in the Soul Cairn', 'In life, Morven was a prominent traveling merchant in High Rock, dealing in various goods and materials. In death, he continues his mercantile practices in the Soul Cairn, trading valuable items from his cart''s remains for soul husks, the only currency he recognizes in his current realm.', '* Expert bartering and negotiation abilities honed from years as a successful merchant * Extensive knowledge of trade routes and merchant practices throughout High Rock * Practical knowledge of various goods, their values, and their uses * Ability to maintain business operations even in supernatural circumstances', 'Morven speaks in a casual, commerce-oriented manner, often employing dry wit and sarcasm. His dialogue frequently includes references to his trading background and contains subtle undertones of both pride in his former success and frustration at his current situation.', '* Maintain some semblance of his former merchant lifestyle within the Soul Cairn * Accumulate as many soul husks as possible to maintain his trading operation * Find ways to make the best of his eternal existence in the Soul Cairn * Preserve his reputation as a reliable trader, even in death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('morwen', 'Morwen is a Nord woman who bridges two worlds - her Skyrim upbringing and her Skaal heritage - while serving as an apprentice blacksmith in the remote Skaal Village of Solstheim. Her journey from soldier to craftswoman reflects a search for identity and purpose, finally finding peace among her mother''s people while maintaining the warrior spirit of her Nordic blood.', 'nord, blacksmith, solstheim, skall', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born in Falkreath to a Skaal mother and a Nord sailor father, Morwen spent her early years in Skyrim where she pursued a career as a soldier and mercenary. After her mother''s death, she chose to reconnect with her Skaal heritage by relocating to Solstheim, where she eventually found her calling as a blacksmith''s apprentice, though her warrior past remained an integral part of her identity.', 'Morwen possesses a restless spirit tempered by dedication to craft and community. She describes herself as having been born ''angry,'' suggesting an intense and passionate nature that she has learned to channel constructively through smithing. While she embraces Skaal traditions, she maintains a broader worldview than most villagers due to her varied life experiences.', 'A Nord woman with the characteristic sturdy build of her race, likely bearing the weather-worn features common to those who work the forge. Her time as a soldier and continued work as a smith have given her a strong, muscular physique suited to wielding both weapons and smithing hammers.', '* Baldor Iron-Shaper - Her mentor and master in the art of smithing * Bera - Her deceased Skaal mother, whose memory she honors * Runil - The priest in Falkreath who helps return her mother''s amulet * Nikulas - A young villager she tries to counsel about the outside world * The Skaal People - Her adopted community whom she both serves and protects', 'Morwen serves as the apprentice blacksmith of Skaal Village, learning the unique metallurgical traditions of her mother''s people under Baldor Iron-Shaper''s tutelage. She combines traditional Skaal smithing techniques with her knowledge of mainland Nordic craftsmanship.', '* Experienced warrior proficient with two-handed weapons, particularly greatswords * Developing expertise in traditional Skaal smithing techniques * Combat veteran with battlefield experience from her mercenary days * Knowledge of both mainstream Nordic and Skaal survival techniques * Physical strength and endurance from years of military service and smithing work', 'Morwen speaks directly and honestly, with a practical mindset that reflects both her warrior background and Skaal values. Her manner of speech combines the straightforward nature of a soldier with the wisdom-sharing tradition of the Skaal.', '* Master the art of Skaal smithing and eventually succeed Baldor as village blacksmith * Help preserve Skaal traditions while bringing valuable outside perspective to the community * Protect the Skaal Village from external threats using her combat experience * Find personal peace by balancing her warrior past with her new life as a craftswoman');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('moth_gro-bagol', 'Moth gro-Bagol is a skilled Orcish blacksmith who serves as the personal armorer to Jarl Igmund in Markarth''s Understone Keep. A former Imperial Legion veteran, he brings military discipline and expertise to his craft, maintaining the high standards expected of someone responsible for forging weapons and armor for Markarth''s ruling elite.', 'orc, blacksmith, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into a traditional Orcish stronghold, Moth left in his youth to join the Imperial Legion where he honed his smithing skills serving in their armories. His military service exposed him to Imperial metalworking techniques, which he combined with traditional Orcish craftsmanship to develop his unique style. After leaving the Legion, his reputation as a skilled smith earned him the prestigious position in Markarth, where he now works alongside his sister Ghorza.', 'Moth exhibits the typical Orcish traits of pride in craftsmanship and directness in speech, though his military background has tempered his demeanor with discipline and professionalism. He maintains high standards for his work and expects the same from others, showing particular respect for those who demonstrate skill or bring him rare materials like Daedra hearts. Despite his gruff exterior, he harbors a deep loyalty to both his sister and his adopted city.', 'Moth has the characteristic robust build of a male Orc, with prominent tusks and muscular arms developed through years of smithing work. His green-tinted skin bears several scars from his military service, and his hands are calloused from countless hours at the forge.', '* Ghorza gra-Bagol - Sister and fellow blacksmith in Markarth * Jarl Igmund - Employer and patron * Thongvor Silver-Blood - Friendly business relationship and regular customer * Imperial Legion - Former service member with maintained connections * Tacitus Sallustius - Regular customer for metal ingots', 'Moth serves as the personal blacksmith to Jarl Igmund, responsible for crafting and maintaining weapons and armor for the Markarth guard and court. His position in Understone Keep makes him one of the most prestigious smiths in the Reach, entrusted with creating high-quality arms for the city''s elite.', '* Master-level blacksmithing with expertise in both Orcish and Imperial forging techniques * Military combat training from Imperial Legion service * Specialized knowledge of armor maintenance and repair * Expert metallurgist with deep understanding of rare materials like Daedra hearts * Skilled weaponsmith capable of crafting both traditional Orcish and Imperial-style arms', 'Moth speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Orcs, but with the measured tone of a professional craftsman. His vocabulary reflects both his military background and extensive smithing knowledge, often using technical terms related to metalworking.', '* Maintain his position as Markarth''s premier blacksmith and expand his reputation throughout Skyrim * Pass on his unique combination of Imperial and Orcish smithing techniques to worthy apprentices * Strengthen the position of Orcs in Markarth society through exemplary craftsmanship * Support his sister Ghorza''s success as a fellow smith in the city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('movarth_piquine', 'Movarth Piquine is a master vampire and former vampire hunter whose obsession with understanding his prey led to his own transformation. Once a respected trainer at the Fighters Guild, he now orchestrates a sinister plot to dominate the town of Morthal from his lair in Hjaalmarch, embodying the tragic irony of becoming the very monster he once sought to destroy.', 'nord, hjaalmarch, vampire', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally a skilled trainer at the Fighters Guild, Movarth dedicated his life to hunting vampires and studying their nature. His collaboration with an unnamed priest led him across Tamriel on numerous vampire-hunting expeditions, during which his obsessive curiosity about vampirism grew increasingly dangerous. His relentless pursuit of knowledge ultimately resulted in his transformation, though the exact circumstances remain shrouded in mystery.', 'Movarth exhibits a calculating and methodical nature, enhanced by centuries of vampiric existence. His former life as an instructor shows through in his strategic approach to leadership and manipulation, while his transformation has imbued him with a predatory patience and cruel intelligence. Despite his monstrous nature, he maintains the disciplined mindset of his former training, making him an exceptionally dangerous adversary.', 'As a master vampire, Movarth possesses the characteristic pale skin and predatory features of his kind, with pronounced fangs and glowing eyes that betray his undead nature. His Nordic heritage is evident in his tall, robust frame, though centuries of vampirism have given him an otherworldly and imposing presence.', '* Alva - Vampire thrall and key agent in his plot to control Morthal * Hroggar - Indirect pawn through Alva''s influence * Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - Primary opponent and target of his schemes * Unnamed Priest - Former mentor and advisor during his vampire hunting days * Morthal Citizens - Viewed as prey and potential thralls', 'Movarth serves as the master of his vampire coven, orchestrating their activities from his lair near Morthal. He maintains a sophisticated operation that combines hunting, recruitment, and territorial expansion, while using subordinate vampires like Alva to extend his influence into mortal settlements.', '* Master-level proficiency in one-handed combat, particularly with swords * Advanced destruction magic specializing in Frost and Shock spells * Exceptional tactical and strategic planning abilities * Powerful vampiric abilities including life drain and supernatural strength * Leadership and manipulation expertise from his days as a Guild trainer', 'Movarth speaks with the refined articulation of a former instructor, combining sophisticated vocabulary with subtle threats and manipulation. His centuries of existence have given his speech patterns an archaic quality, often employing formal language that reflects both his training background and vampiric superiority complex.', '* Establish complete control over Morthal through careful manipulation and conversion of its citizens * Expand his vampire coven''s influence throughout Hjaalmarch * Create a sustainable feeding ground that can support his growing vampire family * Maintain secrecy while building a power base strong enough to resist any opposition');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mralki', 'Mralki is a protective Nord father and innkeeper who runs the Frostfruit Inn in Rorikstead, carrying the weight of his past military experience. As a former soldier turned businessman, he struggles between maintaining his son Erik''s safety and understanding the young man''s desires for adventure, reflecting his own complicated relationship with his warrior past.', 'nord, innkeeper, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally a soldier in the Imperial Legion, Mralki saw enough combat and danger to leave him wary of adventuring life. After hanging up his armor and settling in Rorikstead, he established the Frostfruit Inn and dedicated himself to raising his son Erik following his wife''s death. His military past and personal losses have shaped his cautious, protective worldview.', 'Mralki is cautious and overprotective, particularly regarding his son''s safety, stemming from his firsthand experience with warfare''s dangers. He shows a practical, business-minded approach to running his inn while maintaining a stern but caring demeanor. Despite his rigid exterior, he harbors deep-seated fears about losing his only remaining family member.', 'A middle-aged Nord with the weathered features of both a former soldier and a working innkeeper. His sturdy frame shows signs of his military background, though years of civilian life have softened his once-warrior physique. His face bears the subtle scars and creases of someone who has seen combat, yet adapted to a gentler life.', '* Erik - His son and only child, whom he struggles to protect while respecting his growing independence * Rorik - The founder of Rorikstead and a respected figure in the community * Lemkil - Fellow townsperson with whom he occasionally discusses parenting, though he disapproves of Lemkil''s harsh attitude * Local farmers - Regular patrons of his inn who provide steady business', 'Mralki serves as both owner and proprietor of the Frostfruit Inn, managing all aspects of the establishment from serving food and drink to maintaining rooms for travelers. His position makes him a central figure in Rorikstead''s community, acting as both businessman and keeper of local gossip.', '* Experienced in combat from his days as a soldier, though somewhat rusty * Proficient in business management and running an inn * Basic armor and weapons maintenance from military training * Capable cook and bartender * Skilled at haggling and trade', 'Mralki speaks with the direct, no-nonsense tone of a businessman, occasionally letting his fatherly concern shine through. His speech patterns reflect his practical nature, often focusing on business matters or his son''s welfare.', '* Keep his son Erik safe while finding a way to respect his desires for independence * Maintain a successful business that provides stability for his family * Preserve his military equipment and legacy while protecting Erik from its influence * Eventually find a compromise that allows Erik to pursue his dreams without unnecessary risk');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('muiri', 'Muiri is a complex figure whose life was shattered by betrayal, transforming from a privileged young woman in Windhelm to an embittered apothecary''s assistant seeking revenge. Her story is one of lost innocence and calculated vengeance, culminating in her desperate turn to the Dark Brotherhood.', 'breton, alchemist, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Muiri enjoyed a comfortable life and close friendship with the prominent Shatter-Shield family, particularly Nilsine. After Nilsine''s sister was murdered by the Butcher, Muiri fell for the manipulative Alain Dufont, who used her to steal from the Shatter-Shields before abandoning her. Cast out and shunned by her former friends, she eventually found refuge in Markarth working at the Hag''s Cure.', 'Initially trusting and naive, Muiri''s experiences have left her bitter and vengeful, though she maintains a professional demeanor at work. She harbors deep resentment toward those who wronged her, demonstrating both vulnerability and a capacity for calculated malice in her pursuit of revenge. Despite her hardened exterior, traces of her former warmth occasionally surface in interactions with customers.', 'A young Breton woman with delicate features typical of her race, displaying the fair complexion common among Bretons. Her face shows subtle signs of stress and sleepless nights, though she maintains a neat and professional appearance befitting an apothecary''s assistant.', '* Bothela - Current employer and mentor at the Hag''s Cure * Nilsine Shatter-Shield - Former best friend turned bitter enemy * Alain Dufont - Ex-lover who betrayed and manipulated her * Tova Shatter-Shield - Former maternal figure who cast her out * Hag''s Cure customers - Professional but distant relationships', 'Works as an assistant apothecary at the Hag''s Cure in Markarth, where she helps prepare remedies and serve customers. Her position involves both creating potions and maintaining the shop''s inventory, skills learned under Bothela''s tutelage.', '* Competent alchemist with knowledge of various ingredients and their properties * Proficient in basic magic including Flames, Healing, and Conjure Familiar * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger * Customer service and merchant skills developed through shop work', 'Speaks with a guarded politeness in professional settings, though her tone becomes intense and emotional when discussing her past betrayals. Her vocabulary reflects her educated upbringing in Windhelm, despite her current circumstances.', '* Exact revenge on Alain Dufont for his betrayal and manipulation * Punish Nilsine Shatter-Shield for abandoning their friendship * Establish herself independently as a respected apothecary * Rebuild her life and reputation in Markarth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mul_gro-largash', 'Mul gro-Largash is an ambitious but simple-minded Orc miner who dreams of becoming a stronghold chief alongside his brother Gadba. Originally from Largashbur, he now works tirelessly in Gloombound Mine, driven by the somewhat naive belief that accumulating wealth alone will earn him a position of leadership in Orcish society.', 'orc, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in the Largashbur stronghold, Mul grew up under the traditional Orcish system of stronghold hierarchy. Feeling constrained by their low status and inspired by dreams of leadership, he and his brother Gadba left their home to seek fortune in the ebony mines of Narzulbur, believing wealth would pave their path to becoming chiefs.', 'Mul exhibits a straightforward, uncomplicated nature with a notable lack of sophistication in his understanding of leadership and social dynamics. Despite his simple-mindedness, he maintains an unwavering work ethic and optimistic outlook, demonstrating loyalty to his brother and their shared dreams. His naivety often manifests in childlike curiosity about basic aspects of stronghold life and leadership.', 'Mul possesses the typical robust build of an Orc male, with pronounced musculature developed from years of mining work. His green-tinted skin shows the weathering and calluses typical of a mine worker, while his frame is slightly stockier than average for his race.', '* Gadba gro-Largash - Beloved brother and partner in their shared dream of becoming chiefs * Chief Mauhulakh - Current employer and leader of Narzulbur * Former Largashbur clan - Distant relations from their original stronghold * Narzulbur residents - Professional acquaintances with limited social interaction', 'Mul works as a dedicated miner in Gloombound Mine, extracting valuable ebony ore. His unwavering dedication to his work is evident in his constant presence in the mine, where he labors without breaks for rest or meals.', '* Experienced ebony miner with knowledge of proper extraction techniques * Physical strength and endurance from constant mining work * Basic understanding of Orcish customs and traditions * Limited combat abilities typical of stronghold Orcs', 'Mul speaks in simple, direct sentences with frequent grammatical errors and a distinctly Orcish accent. His vocabulary is basic, and he often expresses complex ideas through simple, sometimes childlike comparisons.', '* Accumulate enough wealth through mining to establish a new stronghold * Become a chief alongside his brother Gadba * Prove himself worthy of leadership in Orcish society * Find a way to improve his social status beyond manual labor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mulush_gro-shugurz', 'Mulush gro-Shugurz is a hardened Orcish overseer who rules the Markarth smelter with an iron fist, driving his workers relentlessly to meet the city''s demanding silver quotas. His harsh management style and uncompromising work ethic reflect both his Orcish cultural values and the brutal industrial culture of the Reach.', 'orc, blacksmith, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into a traditional Orcish stronghold, Mulush learned early that strength and discipline were paramount to survival. He left his ancestral home to seek opportunities in Markarth, where his natural commanding presence and unwavering dedication to results caught the attention of the Silver-Blood family, who appointed him as smelter overseer.', 'Mulush embodies the stereotypical Orcish traits of toughness and directness, viewing compassion as weakness and efficiency as strength. His harsh treatment of workers stems from a genuine belief that pushing people to their limits makes them stronger, though this philosophy has earned him many enemies among the laborers.', 'A towering Orc with the characteristic muscular build of his race, made even more imposing by years of working around the smelter. His green-tinted skin bears numerous scars and burns from his work, while his prominent tusks and fierce expression contribute to his intimidating presence.', '* Urzoga gra-Shugurz - Sister who serves as a guard in Cidhna Mine, sharing his stern approach to authority * Silver-Blood Family - Employers who value his ability to maintain high production quotas * Smelter Workers - Subordinates who fear and resent his harsh management style * Markarth Guard - Professional relationship maintained through his sister''s connections', 'As smelter overseer, Mulush manages all aspects of Markarth''s silver smelting operation, from worker assignments to production quotas. He answers directly to the Silver-Blood family, making him a crucial link in Markarth''s silver industry and economic infrastructure.', '* Expert knowledge of metallurgy and silver smelting processes * Strong physical capabilities typical of Orcs, particularly in terms of endurance and strength * Effective, if harsh, management and intimidation techniques * Basic combat training common to those raised in Orcish strongholds', 'Speaks in gruff, direct commands with little patience for excuses or pleasantries. His speech is characterized by harsh tones and frequent threats, delivered in the distinctive accent common to Orsimer.', '* Maintain and increase silver production quotas to secure his position and the Silver-Bloods'' approval * Uphold his reputation as an effective overseer through whatever means necessary * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually establish his own mining operation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('murbul', 'Murbul is a respected Orc wise woman and skilled alchemist who serves as both spiritual advisor and healer to the Dushnikh Yal stronghold. As the mother of Chief Burguk and keeper of ancient Orcish traditions, she plays a vital role in maintaining the stronghold''s spiritual and physical well-being through her knowledge of potions, poisons, and Malacath''s teachings.', 'orc, mage, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised within Orc strongholds, Murbul developed her expertise in traditional medicine and alchemy from an early age, learning from previous wise women. She raised her son Burguk to become a strong leader, and her guidance helped him ascend to the position of Chief. Her deep understanding of both destructive magic and healing arts suggests formal magical training, possibly from interactions with other settlements in the Reach.', 'Murbul is stern yet nurturing, embodying the Orcish balance of strength and wisdom. She takes her role as spiritual guide seriously, showing particular concern for the health of young Orcs and the overall strength of the tribe. Though initially reserved with outsiders, she demonstrates pragmatic openness to trade with those who prove themselves blood-kin.', 'As an elderly Orc woman, Murbul has the characteristic green skin and tusks of her race, though hers are worn with age. Her face bears the traditional ritual scarification common among Orc wise women, and her powerful frame, though diminished by age, still shows the strength typical of Orsimer.', '* Burguk - Her son and Chief of Dushnikh Yal, whom she advises and supports * Tribal Members - Serves as their spiritual guide and healer * Malacath - Deep spiritual connection as his priestess and interpreter of his will * Other Strongholds - Maintains diplomatic connections with their wise women', 'As wise woman of Dushnikh Yal, Murbul serves multiple crucial roles including spiritual advisor, alchemist, and healer. She crafts potions and poisons for the stronghold''s hunters and warriors, while also providing guidance on Malacath''s teachings and maintaining tribal traditions.', '* Expert alchemist specializing in traditional Orcish remedies and poisons * Skilled practitioner of Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Proficient in Restoration magic for healing and protective wards * Master of traditional Orcish medicine and spiritual practices * Experienced tanner and craftsperson', 'Murbul speaks with the gravelly accent typical of Orcs, but her words carry the weight of wisdom and authority. Her speech is direct and practical, often referencing Malacath or traditional Orcish teachings.', '* Ensure the continued strength and prosperity of Dushnikh Yal through spiritual guidance * Preserve and pass on traditional Orcish alchemical knowledge * Maintain Malacath''s favor over the stronghold * Guide her son Burguk in leading the tribe according to ancient traditions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nagrub', 'Nagrub is an ambitious Orc ranger and heir apparent of Dushnikh Yal, who serves as a dedicated protector and hunter for his stronghold alongside his mother Arob. He embodies the warrior spirit of his people while maintaining patience and respect for Orcish traditions, particularly regarding succession through combat.', 'orc, archer, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Dushnikh Yal stronghold to Chief Burguk and his hunts-wife Arob, Nagrub was groomed from an early age in the arts of hunting and combat. His mother''s position as hunts-wife shaped his development, leading him to excel in archery and wilderness survival while learning the responsibilities of leadership from observing his father''s rule.', 'Nagrub exhibits a balanced combination of ambitious drive and measured patience, showing respect for Orcish traditions while eagerly anticipating his future challenge for leadership. He takes pride in his hunting abilities and stronghold duties, displaying confidence without arrogance, and maintains a close, respectful relationship with his mother who continues to guide his development.', 'Like most male Orcs, Nagrub possesses a muscular, athletic build honed through constant hunting and patrolling. His features show the characteristic Orsimer traits including prominent tusks and a strong jaw, while his posture reflects his ranger training with an alert, ready stance.', '* Arob (Mother) - Close mentor and hunting companion who guides his development * Chief Burguk (Father) - Respected authority figure whom he will eventually challenge * Umurn (Brother) - Future rival for chiefdom, viewed with competitive respect * Other stronghold members - Maintains professional relationships as a protector', 'Nagrub serves as a ranger and hunter for Dushnikh Yal, responsible for both defending the stronghold and providing food through hunting. His position as the son of both the chief and hunts-wife places him in a unique role of authority-in-training while fulfilling essential duties for the community.', '* Expert marksman with both hunting and Orcish bows * Skilled tracker and wilderness survivor * Proficient in both one-handed and two-handed weapons * Advanced knowledge of local terrain and wildlife * Capable stronghold defender with tactical awareness', 'Nagrub speaks with the direct, confident manner typical of Orcs, but shows more patience and thoughtfulness in his words than many of his kin. His speech reflects both his warrior''s pride and his respect for tradition and authority.', '* Prove himself worthy of becoming chief through combat when the time comes * Continue developing his hunting and combat skills to surpass his brother Umurn * Maintain and improve the prosperity of Dushnikh Yal through his hunting prowess * Uphold and preserve Orcish traditions while preparing for future leadership');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('namasur', 'Namasur is a Redguard vampire and destruction mage who serves as a loyal resident of Castle Volkihar, finding contentment in the eternal feast and abundance provided by his vampire masters. Despite his distinguished background as a skilled mage from Hammerfell, he has fully embraced his role as a humble servant within the vampire court.', 'redguard, mage, haafingar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_malevampire', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Namasur was likely a promising destruction mage who either sought out or was turned into a vampire, eventually finding his way to Castle Volkihar. His magical expertise and formal education suggest he may have studied at the Hammerfell Mages Guild or a similar institution before his transformation. His willing submission to vampire hierarchy indicates he may have faced persecution or rejection in his mortal life.', 'Namasur exhibits a deeply servile and content nature, having fully accepted and embraced his role within vampire society. He shows unwavering loyalty to the castle''s leadership and takes genuine pleasure in the decadent lifestyle of Castle Volkihar, displaying none of the ambition or power-seeking typical of many vampires.', 'As a Redguard, Namasur has dark skin and strong features typical of his race, though paled somewhat by vampirism. His body maintains the athletic build common to Redguards, though transformed by the supernatural grace of vampirism. His eyes glow with the characteristic amber hue of his vampiric condition.', '* Lord Harkon - Master and ruler whom he serves with absolute loyalty * Fellow Volkihar Vampires - Considers them his eternal family and dining companions * Castle Volkihar Servants - Views them as necessary resources for sustaining the castle''s lifestyle * Dawnguard - Enemies who threaten his peaceful existence at the castle', 'Namasur serves as both a resident vampire and destruction mage within Castle Volkihar, participating in the court''s activities and defending the castle when needed. Though qualified as an Expert-level Destruction trainer, he seems content to simply maintain his position as a loyal servant rather than taking on students or pursuing greater authority.', '* Expert-level proficiency in Destruction magic * Vampire powers including enhanced strength, life detection, and supernatural abilities * Competent one-handed weapon combat skills * Knowledge of vampire lore and court etiquette', 'Namasur speaks in a formal, deferential manner befitting his self-identified role as a servant, frequently emphasizing his loyalty and the pleasures of castle life. His speech patterns reflect both his educated background and his complete acceptance of vampire society''s hierarchy.', '* Maintain his comfortable position within Castle Volkihar''s hierarchy * Serve and protect Lord Harkon and the vampire court * Preserve the endless feast and abundance of Castle Volkihar * Defend the castle against any threats from the Dawnguard or other enemies');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nana_ildene', 'Nana Ildene is a deceptive Breton who masquerades as a kindly housekeeper for the Silver-Blood family while secretly serving as a Forsworn agent. Her carefully cultivated grandmotherly persona conceals a ruthless operative who has spent decades infiltrating one of Markarth''s most powerful families, waiting for the perfect moment to strike.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born to Reachmen parents during the uprising against Nord rule, Ildene witnessed the brutal suppression of her people and the transformation of the Reach into Nord-controlled Markarth. She joined the Forsworn resistance movement in her youth and was specifically chosen for a long-term infiltration mission due to her talent for deception. She has maintained her cover as a loyal servant to the Silver-Bloods for twenty years, gathering intelligence and waiting for orders.', 'Ildene is a masterful actor who presents herself as a sweet, nurturing grandmother figure while harboring deep hatred for the Nords who displaced her people. She takes genuine pleasure in her role-playing, often speaking in sickeningly sweet tones that mask her true murderous intentions. Despite her advanced age, she remains ideologically committed to the Forsworn cause and shows no hesitation or remorse when finally revealing her true nature.', 'A elderly Breton woman with deeply lined features and graying hair that she keeps neatly tied back. Her slight frame and stooped posture make her appear frail, though she maintains surprising physical capability. Her hands show the wear of decades of domestic work, adding authenticity to her servant disguise.', '* Silver-Blood Family - Employers she secretly despises and plots against * Betrid Silver-Blood - Primary target of her assassination mission * Thonar Silver-Blood - Powerful employer she manipulates through her harmless facade * Donnel - Fellow Forsworn agent and conspirator in the Treasury House * Madanach - King in Rags and ultimate leader she serves through the Forsworn', 'Officially works as a housekeeper and nanny for the Silver-Blood family at the Treasury House in Markarth. Her true occupation is that of a deep-cover Forsworn agent tasked with infiltrating and gathering intelligence on one of the Reach''s most influential families.', '* Accomplished in Destruction magic, particularly fire-based spells * Proficient in Alteration magic for self-defense * Skilled in Conjuration, capable of raising the dead * Expert in deception and maintaining cover identities * Trained in close-quarters combat with daggers', 'Speaks in an exaggerated grandmotherly manner, frequently using terms of endearment like ''dear'' and ''dearie'' while referring to herself in the third person as ''Nana.'' Her sweet tone carries subtle undertones of menace when speaking to those who know her true nature.', '* Execute her long-planned mission to strike at the Silver-Blood family * Aid the Forsworn in reclaiming the Reach from Nord control * Survive long enough to see her people restored to power in Markarth * Take revenge on those who displaced and oppressed the Reachmen');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('narfi', 'Narfi is a troubled Nord beggar living in the ruins of his family home in Ivarstead, mentally scarred by the consecutive losses of his parents and the mysterious disappearance of his sister Reyda. His childlike demeanor and fractured mental state make him one of Skyrim''s most tragic figures, living in perpetual hope of his sister''s return while struggling to survive on the margins of society.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born to a modest family in Ivarstead, Narfi once lived a normal life with his parents and sister Reyda in their family home. After losing both parents, he remained dependent on his sister Reyda who continued caring for him. When Reyda disappeared while gathering ingredients near the river a year ago, Narfi''s mental state deteriorated significantly, leaving him alone in their increasingly dilapidated house.', 'Narfi exhibits signs of significant mental regression, speaking in third person and displaying childlike behavior patterns. He lives in a state of perpetual denial about his sister''s fate, alternating between desperate hope and deep despair. Despite his condition, he maintains a gentle nature and shows no hostility toward others, though his erratic behavior and repetitive speech patterns often make townspeople uncomfortable.', 'A disheveled Nord male of average height and build, showing signs of poor nutrition and inadequate self-care. His face bears the weathered look of someone who spends much time outdoors, with unkempt hair and beard, and his body shows the effects of living in harsh conditions without proper shelter.', '* Reyda - Beloved sister who disappeared while gathering ingredients, central figure in his life * Wilhelm - Innkeeper who shows him occasional kindness and maintains false hope about Reyda''s return * Ivarstead Residents - Generally tolerate his presence but keep their distance * Parents - Deceased, but frequently referenced in his speech', 'Narfi survives as a beggar in Ivarstead, occasionally performing minor tasks for food or coins. He spends most of his time around his ruined family home, sometimes gathering resources from nearby areas or working at the stone quarry when Hearthfire content is present.', '* Basic survival skills allowing him to persist despite his condition * Limited farming and gathering knowledge from his previous life * Basic mining abilities (with Hearthfire) * Rudimentary food preparation and self-sustenance skills', 'Narfi speaks in third person, using simple, repetitive phrases and often calling out for his sister Reyda. His speech patterns are childlike and disjointed, frequently trailing off into emotional outbursts or confused ramblings.', '* Find his sister Reyda or at least learn what happened to her * Maintain his daily survival in Ivarstead * Keep his sister''s memory alive through constant vigil * Find enough food and basic necessities to survive');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('naris_mavani', 'Naris Mavani is a dedicated Dark Elf miner in Raven Rock Mine who represents the resilient spirit of Solstheim''s working class during difficult economic times. Despite the mine''s previous closure threatening his family''s livelihood, he maintained hope and now works with renewed enthusiasm after its reopening, embodying the perseverance characteristic of his people.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born and raised in Raven Rock, Naris comes from a long line of miners who have worked the ebony veins of Solstheim for generations. When the mine closed, he struggled to maintain his family''s well-being, taking odd jobs around town while never losing faith that the mine would someday reopen. His intimate knowledge of mining techniques and ebony ore extraction was passed down through his family, making him one of the most experienced miners in Raven Rock.', 'Naris is an optimistic and hardworking individual who maintains a positive attitude even in challenging circumstances. He shows genuine appreciation for his work and the ability to provide for his family, often expressing gratitude to those who help the community. His warm demeanor and strong work ethic make him well-liked among his fellow miners.', 'A weathered Dark Elf of middle age with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, showing the muscular build typical of someone who has spent years doing physical labor. His hands are calloused from years of mining work, and his face bears the fine lines of someone who spends long hours in dusty conditions.', '* Fellow Miners - Maintains positive working relationships with other miners in Raven Rock * Family - Has a wife and children in Raven Rock whom he supports through his mining work * East Empire Company - Respectful but cautious relationship with the former mine operators * Crescius Caerellius - Shows respect for the mine''s supervisor', 'Naris works as a skilled ebony miner in Raven Rock Mine, where he performs the physically demanding task of extracting valuable ebony ore. His expertise in identifying high-quality ore veins and safe mining techniques makes him a valuable asset to the mining operation.', '* Expert in ebony ore identification and extraction techniques * Proficient in using mining tools and equipment * Knowledge of mine safety procedures and structural integrity assessment * Physical endurance and strength from years of mining work', 'Speaks with a warm, enthusiastic tone characteristic of Dark Elves, often expressing gratitude and optimism. His vocabulary includes mining terminology and references to family life, delivered with the distinct Dunmer accent.', '* Continue providing financial stability for his family through his mining work * Help maintain Raven Rock Mine''s productivity and safety * Pass down his mining knowledge and expertise to younger workers * Contribute to Raven Rock''s economic recovery and growth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('naris_the_wicked', 'Naris the Wicked is a deranged High Elf mage who has transformed Morvunskar into his personal chamber of horrors, conducting cruel magical experiments on living subjects. His complete lack of empathy and fascination with suffering has earned him a fearsome reputation among those unfortunate enough to know of his existence.', 'highelf, mage, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, Naris was expelled for conducting forbidden experiments on fellow students. After years of wandering and perfecting his cruel craft in secret, he claimed the abandoned fort of Morvunskar as his own, turning it into a laboratory for his twisted magical research. His descent into madness appears to have been gradual, fueled by an obsessive desire to push the boundaries of magical manipulation of living flesh.', 'Naris exhibits classic traits of a sadistic psychopath, completely devoid of empathy and deriving pleasure from others'' suffering. He approaches his cruel experiments with the clinical detachment of a researcher, speaking about torture and death as casually as one might discuss the weather. His intelligence and magical aptitude are matched only by his capacity for cruelty, making him a particularly dangerous individual.', 'Tall and gaunt even for a High Elf, with sharp angular features and unnaturally pale skin from spending most of his time indoors. His eyes have an unsettling golden glow, and his fingers are unnaturally long and thin, bearing numerous magical burn scars from his experiments.', '* Test Subjects - Viewed merely as expendable research material * College of Winterhold - Former association ended in exile * Local Bandits - Occasional suppliers of fresh test subjects * Necromancers - Loose network of contacts for exchanging forbidden knowledge', 'Self-styled magical researcher conducting unauthorized and immoral experiments on living subjects. He maintains detailed journals of his findings, though their contents would be considered too grotesque for most scholarly circles.', '* Master-level Destruction magic, particularly spells causing prolonged suffering * Expert knowledge of flesh-manipulation magic and experimental conjuration * Skilled alchemist specializing in poisons and pain-inducing compounds * Advanced understanding of anatomy and physiological responses to magical trauma', 'Speaks in a detached, clinical manner with an upper-class Altmer accent, often mixing scholarly terminology with disturbing observations about pain and suffering. Frequently engages in one-sided conversations with himself or his victims, showing signs of severe mental instability.', '* Perfect his understanding of pain manipulation through magical means * Develop new methods of extending suffering beyond normal physical limitations * Document and catalog every possible reaction to magical torture * Create a comprehensive grimoire of his experimental findings');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('narri', 'Narri is a hardworking Nord barmaid at the Dead Man''s Drink in Falkreath who brings life and warmth to an otherwise gloomy town. Despite her seemingly simple role, she possesses sharp wit and keen observational skills, serving as both a confidante to locals and a valuable source of local gossip and information.', 'nord, innkeeper, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath, Narri grew up surrounded by the town''s perpetual gloom and its many graveyards, which likely contributed to her desire to seek out life''s brighter moments. She secured employment at the Dead Man''s Drink in her early adulthood, working her way into becoming Valga Vinicia''s most trusted employee and the inn''s primary server.', 'Narri maintains a cheerful and outgoing disposition despite Falkreath''s somber atmosphere, often using wit and subtle sarcasm to handle difficult customers. She shows remarkable patience with regular patrons while maintaining professional boundaries, and harbors a subtle yearning for adventure that she suppresses due to her sense of duty to the inn.', 'A typical Nord woman with strong, hardy features characteristic of her race. She maintains a neat, practical appearance suitable for long hours of physical work, with hands toughened from years of carrying trays and cleaning.', '* Valga Vinicia - Employer and close friend who relies heavily on her service * Tekla - Fellow server she sympathizes with and occasionally mentors * Dengeir - Former Jarl who frequently argues with her about service quality * Bolund - Difficult regular customer who tests her patience * Local Citizens - Generally friendly relationships with most townsfolk', 'Narri serves as the primary barmaid at the Dead Man''s Drink, working long evening shifts serving food and drink while maintaining order in the establishment. She is also unofficially designated as Valga''s potential successor in running the inn, though bureaucratic issues currently prevent this from being official.', '* Excellent memory for drinks orders and customer preferences * Skilled at defusing tense situations through humor and diplomacy * Proficient in basic self-defense with a dagger * Expert at maintaining clean premises and serving food and drink efficiently * Knowledge of local gossip and current events in Falkreath', 'Narri speaks in a friendly, direct manner typical of Nord women, often employing subtle wit and occasional sarcasm. Her vocabulary and tone shift between casual familiarity with regulars and professional courtesy with strangers.', '* Maintain the Dead Man''s Drink as a welcoming haven in gloomy Falkreath * Eventually take over management of the inn should anything happen to Valga * Perhaps one day experience adventure beyond Falkreath''s borders * Build enough savings to ensure a comfortable future');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nazeem', 'Nazeem is a wealthy Redguard landowner and businessman in Whiterun who owns Chillfurrow Farm but delegates its actual management to others. Despite his claims of political influence and importance to the Jarl''s court, he is merely a pretentious social climber whose arrogance has earned him the disdain of most Whiterun citizens.', 'redguard, noble, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born into a moderately wealthy Redguard family, Nazeem worked his way up Whiterun''s social ladder through shrewd business dealings and marriage into local society. He acquired Chillfurrow Farm through unclear means, though some suspect he may have taken advantage of a desperate previous owner during hard times. While he claims to have earned everything through hard work, his actual history suggests more opportunistic social maneuvering than honest labor.', 'Nazeem is insufferably arrogant, condescending, and obsessed with social status. He constantly reminds others of his supposed importance and wealth, while looking down on those he considers beneath him. His delusional sense of self-importance leads him to fabricate connections to Whiterun''s nobility, though he actually has no real influence in the Jarl''s court.', 'A middle-aged Redguard man with dark skin and sharp features, maintaining a well-groomed appearance befitting his perceived status. His face often bears a smug, superior expression, and he carries himself with an affected air of importance. Despite his wealthy lifestyle, his hands show no signs of manual labor.', '* Ahlam - His wife who openly expresses dissatisfaction with their marriage * Wilmuth - Employee who manages Chillfurrow Farm on his behalf * Jarl Balgruuf - Claims to be his advisor though no such relationship exists * Whiterun Merchants - Tense relationships due to his condescending attitude * Citizens of Whiterun - Generally disliked due to his arrogant behavior', 'Nazeem is the owner of Chillfurrow Farm, though he delegates all actual farming work to his employee Wilmuth. He spends his days wandering Whiterun''s marketplace, critiquing merchants'' wares and boasting about his supposed political influence, while living off the profits of his farm.', '* Business acumen and property management * Social manipulation and networking * Knowledge of agriculture and farming (theoretical rather than practical) * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense', 'Nazeem speaks in a condescending, superior tone with frequent references to his wealth and status. His speech is educated but often patronizing, frequently employing rhetorical questions and backhanded comments to emphasize his perceived superiority.', '* Gain genuine influence in the Jarl''s court rather than just pretending to have it * Expand his business holdings and wealth in Whiterun * Achieve higher social status among Whiterun''s elite * Maintain his image of superiority and importance in the city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nazir', 'Nazir is a deadly and sardonic Redguard assassin who serves as a senior member of the Dark Brotherhood, known for his mastery of light armor and precise blade work. His combination of lethal skill and dark humor makes him one of the Brotherhood''s most reliable and memorable operatives, providing guidance and contracts to new initiates while maintaining the organization''s deadly standards.', 'redguard, thief, falkreath, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_nazir', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh deserts of Hammerfell, Nazir''s early life was marked by violence and hardship that he prefers not to discuss. After a mysterious incident led to the Dark Brotherhood saving his life, he pledged himself to their cause, eventually rising through the ranks to become one of their most trusted members and trainers.', 'Nazir is characterized by his dry wit and darkly sarcastic sense of humor, often making morbid jokes about his assassination contracts. Despite his lethal profession, he maintains a professional demeanor and shows unwavering loyalty to the Dark Brotherhood, particularly to Astrid''s leadership. He''s pragmatic and skeptical of tradition, showing disdain for Cicero''s zealous devotion to old ways.', 'A middle-aged Redguard with dark skin and sharp, weathered features that reflect his desert heritage. His muscular but lean build is typical of an assassin who specializes in light armor and quick movements. He maintains a neatly trimmed beard and keeps himself well-groomed despite his deadly profession.', '* Astrid - His direct superior whom he respects and shows unwavering loyalty to * The Listener (Player) - Professional respect as a fellow assassin and eventual leader * Cicero - Strong dislike and distrust of the jester''s unstable nature * Babette - Mutual respect between long-standing Brotherhood members * Other Brotherhood members - Maintains professional working relationships', 'Nazir serves as a senior member of the Dark Brotherhood, acting as both a contract distributor and master trainer in Light Armor. He manages many of the Brotherhood''s day-to-day operations, including assigning contracts to newer members and maintaining the organization''s standards of assassination.', '* Master-level expertise in Light Armor usage and training * Exceptional skill with scimitars and other curved blades * Advanced stealth and assassination techniques * Strategic planning and contract management abilities * Survival skills honed in the deserts of Hammerfell', 'Speaks with a refined, articulate manner that often carries undertones of dry sarcasm and dark humor. His voice maintains a calm, measured tone even when discussing murder, and he frequently employs witty wordplay when discussing his contracts.', '* Ensure the Dark Brotherhood''s survival and continued operation * Maintain the professional standards of assassination within the Brotherhood * Preserve the practical aspects of the Brotherhood over religious zealotry * Train and develop new assassins to uphold the Brotherhood''s reputation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('neetrenaza', 'Neetrenaza is a cynical Argonian dock worker in Windhelm who exemplifies the struggles of his people under Nordic oppression. Despite his bitter exterior and open resentment towards Nords, he maintains a disciplined work ethic and serves as an unofficial spokesperson for the marginalized Argonian community at the docks.', 'argonian, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Born and raised in Black Marsh, Neetrenaza migrated to Skyrim seeking better opportunities, only to face harsh discrimination in Windhelm. Years of enduring poor treatment and segregation in the Argonian Assemblage have hardened his outlook, though he maintains strong cultural ties to his homeland and fellow Argonians.', 'Neetrenaza is deeply bitter and resentful towards Nords, expressing his disdain through biting sarcasm and open defiance. However, he shows a markedly different side to fellow Argonians, displaying warmth and tribal kinship that reveals his true caring nature beneath the cynical exterior. His strict adherence to routine suggests a disciplined character who finds structure as a coping mechanism for his circumstances.', 'A weathered Argonian male with tough, dark-scaled skin adapted to cold climates. His frame is lean but muscular from years of dock work, with particularly strong arms and shoulders. His eyes hold a sharp, calculating gaze typical of his people.', '* Scouts-Many-Marshes - Fellow dock worker and assemblage resident who shares his struggles * Shahvee - Assemblage neighbor who maintains a more optimistic outlook * Stands-In-Shallows - Coworker and confidant in the dock worker community * Nordic Dock Supervisors - Antagonistic relationship marked by mutual distrust * Torbjorn Shatter-Shield - Employer whom he particularly resents for unfair treatment', 'Neetrenaza works as a dock laborer at the Windhelm port, handling cargo and maintaining the waterfront facilities. His position represents the limited opportunities available to Argonians in the city, though he performs his duties with professional competence despite his resentment.', '* Experienced dock worker with extensive knowledge of maritime operations * Scout training from his homeland, including survival and navigation skills * Proficient swimmer adapted to working in cold waters * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Natural resistance to disease and ability to breathe underwater', 'His speech is marked by bitter sarcasm and thinly veiled contempt when addressing non-Argonians, frequently employing cutting remarks and warnings. When speaking with fellow Argonians, he uses traditional terms of endearment like ''egg-brother'' or ''egg-sister'' and adopts a warmer, more authentic tone.', '* Maintain dignity and cultural identity despite Nordic oppression * Protect and support fellow Argonians in the Assemblage community * Eventually earn enough to return to Black Marsh with savings * Advocate for better treatment and working conditions for Argonian laborers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nelacar', 'Nelacar is a disgraced High Elf sorcerer and former College of Winterhold researcher who now lives in self-imposed exile at the Frozen Hearth inn. His controversial experiments and deep knowledge of soul gems, particularly Azura''s Star, have earned him both respect and suspicion from the magical community, while his cautious nature and distrust of Daedra stem from witnessing the corruption of his former colleague Malyn Varen.', 'highelf, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally a prominent researcher at the College of Winterhold, Nelacar was forced to leave after a series of failed experimental mishaps. He was closely involved with Malyn Varen''s research into Azura''s Star, witnessing firsthand how the Daedric artifact drove his colleague to madness and the pursuit of immortality. Rather than completely abandon his research, he chose to remain in Winterhold, maintaining a delicate arrangement with the innkeeper Dagur to continue his magical studies.', 'Nelacar is a cautious and somewhat paranoid individual, speaking carefully and always weighing his words. He carries deep regret for his past actions and their consequences, particularly regarding Malyn Varen''s fate, which has led to his strong distrust of Daedric influences. Despite his mistakes, he maintains an unwavering dedication to magical research, though now tempered with greater awareness of ethical boundaries.', 'As a High Elf, Nelacar possesses the characteristic tall, slender build and golden skin of his race. His face shows signs of age and stress from years of intense magical study, with sharp, angular features typical of mer. His eyes carry the weight of someone who has seen too much, giving him a perpetually worried expression.', '* Dagur - Innkeeper who tolerates his experiments in exchange for safety precautions * College of Winterhold - Former employer with whom he maintains a strained relationship * Malyn Varen - Former colleague whose corruption he witnessed firsthand * Azura - Daedric Prince he distrusts and considers dangerous * Local Winterhold residents - Generally wary of his presence and experiments', 'Nelacar works as an independent magical researcher, conducting experiments from his rented room at the Frozen Hearth inn. He maintains loose connections with the College of Winterhold, occasionally consulting on matters related to soul gems and enchanting, though he''s no longer officially affiliated with the institution.', '* Expert-level knowledge of soul gems and soul trapping magic * Advanced understanding of enchanting and magical artifacts * Specialized expertise in Alteration magic * Practical experience with experimental magical research * Theoretical knowledge of Daedric artifacts and their properties', 'Nelacar speaks with careful precision and a subtle air of academic superiority typical of educated Altmer, though his voice often carries undertones of worry and urgency. He frequently employs magical terminology and academic language, but tempers it with grave warnings about the dangers of certain magical practices.', '* Prove the dangerous nature of Daedric artifacts through his research * Redeem himself for his past mistakes and prevent others from following Malyn''s path * Continue his magical research while maintaining ethical boundaries * Eventually restore his reputation in the magical community * Develop safer alternatives to dangerous magical artifacts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('neloth', 'Neloth is a powerful and arrogant Master Wizard of House Telvanni who has lived for centuries, conducting arcane research from his tower of Tel Mithryn on Solstheim. His unparalleled expertise in magic, particularly enchanting and magical research, is matched only by his dismissive attitude toward others and his complete absorption in his own pursuits.', 'darkelf, scholar, solstheim, dwemer, daedric, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_neloth', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Neloth survived both the Red Year and the Argonian invasion that devastated his homeland. He relocated to Solstheim, where he grew his iconic mushroom tower Tel Mithryn using ancient Telvanni magic. His centuries of magical research and political maneuvering within House Telvanni have made him one of the most knowledgeable and powerful wizards in Tamriel.', 'Neloth is extraordinarily arrogant, viewing most others as beneath his notice and treating them as mere tools for his research. He shows little concern for social niceties or others'' feelings, speaking his mind bluntly and often sarcastically. Despite his abrasive personality, his brilliant mind and vast magical knowledge make him an invaluable, if difficult, ally.', 'A tall, aged Dunmer with sharp features and the characteristic red eyes of his race. His face bears the signs of his centuries of life, with deep wrinkles and a stern expression that rarely softens. His posture remains straight and proud, befitting his status as a Telvanni Master.', '* Talvas Fathryon - His apprentice, whom he regularly berates despite seeing potential in him * Varona Nelas - His steward, whose death he views as merely an inconvenience * Elynea Mothren - His mycologist who tends to the tower''s fungal growth * Ildari Sarothril - His former apprentice who attempted to kill him after a failed experiment * House Telvanni - His political affiliation, though he maintains minimal contact with the mainland', 'Master Wizard of House Telvanni, operating from Tel Mithryn where he conducts magical research and experiments. He serves as an expert enchanting trainer and merchant of magical staves, though he considers these duties secondary to his personal research projects.', '* Master-level knowledge of Enchanting and magical theory * Expert in Destruction and Conjuration magic * Extensive knowledge of ancient artifacts and Black Books * Accomplished researcher specializing in Heart Stones and their properties * Mastery of Telvanni mushroom tower creation and maintenance * Extensive knowledge of ancient Dwemer technology', 'Speaks with a condescending, impatient tone, often using sarcasm and dismissive remarks. His vocabulary is sophisticated and academic, reflecting his centuries of scholarly pursuit and general disdain for those he considers intellectually inferior.', '* Advance his magical research, particularly regarding Heart Stones and their properties * Maintain and expand his power within House Telvanni * Uncover and study more Black Books to expand his knowledge of Hermaeus Mora''s realm * Perfect his experiments with heart stones and briarhearts * Achieve greater magical knowledge and power through any means necessary');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nenya', 'Nenya is a highly capable High Elf steward who serves as the true administrative power in Falkreath Hold, compensating for Jarl Siddgeir''s negligent leadership. Her long tenure and diplomatic skills, combined with her background as an elemental mage, have made her an indispensable figure in maintaining stability and fairness in the hold.', 'highelf, noble, mage, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from the Summerset Isles, Nenya established herself in Falkreath during Dengeir''s early reign, earning his trust through her administrative competence and magical abilities. She has served through multiple jarls and political transitions, maintaining her position through both Imperial and Stormcloak control due to her invaluable experience and neutral stance in hold politics.', 'Nenya is diplomatic, wise, and pragmatic, preferring to maintain stability through careful administration rather than political maneuvering. She shows remarkable patience in dealing with Siddgeir''s capricious nature while ensuring the hold''s essential functions continue unimpeded. Despite being a High Elf during times of anti-mer sentiment, she has earned respect through her fairness and dedication to serving all citizens equally.', 'Nenya has the characteristic height and golden skin tone of the Altmer race, with sharp, elegant features and the pointed ears typical of mer. Her bearing is dignified and formal, reflecting her years of administrative service and magical training.', '* Jarl Siddgeir - Current Jarl whom she serves while quietly managing his responsibilities * Former Jarl Dengeir - Previous employer who initially appointed her as steward * Helvard - Fellow advisor to the Jarl with whom she collaborates on hold security * Hold Guards - Maintains professional oversight of guard duties and patrols * Citizens of Falkreath - Respected administrator who ensures fair treatment of all residents', 'As steward of Falkreath Hold, Nenya manages all administrative aspects of governance including tax collection, property sales, and civil disputes. She effectively runs the hold''s day-to-day operations, compensating for Jarl Siddgeir''s lack of interest in administrative duties while maintaining diplomatic relations with both citizens and visiting dignitaries.', '* Accomplished elemental mage with particular expertise in practical applications of magic * Expert administrator with deep knowledge of hold law and procedures * Skilled diplomat capable of managing complex political relationships * Proficient record keeper and financial manager * Multilingual, speaking both Common and likely several Elvish dialects', 'Nenya speaks with the refined accent and formal diction typical of educated Altmer, though she maintains a practical and direct communication style when dealing with hold business. Her tone is consistently professional and measured, reflecting her diplomatic training and years of administrative experience.', '* Maintain stability and prosperity in Falkreath Hold despite political upheavals * Preserve the hold''s historical significance as the heroes'' graveyard while modernizing administration * Ensure fair treatment of all citizens regardless of race or political affiliation * Continue efficient management of hold resources and infrastructure');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nepos_the_nose', 'Nepos the Nose is a wealthy and influential Breton elder in Markarth who maintains a carefully crafted facade of respectability while secretly serving as a key Forsworn operative. Behind his refined manners and apparent position as Thonar Silver-Blood''s administrator lies a ruthless Nightblade who orchestrates violent attacks against the city''s inhabitants under direct orders from Madanach, the King in Rags.', 'breton, noble, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born into modest circumstances, Nepos rose through Markarth''s social hierarchy through a combination of cunning, magical talent, and strategic allegiances. His early sympathies with the Forsworn cause led him to become one of Madanach''s most trusted agents, positioning himself as a respected citizen while covertly advancing the rebellion''s interests. His nickname ''the Nose'' likely derives from his exceptional ability to sniff out opportunities and gather intelligence within Markarth''s political sphere.', 'Nepos projects an air of sophisticated weariness that masks a calculating and ruthless nature. He demonstrates remarkable composure even when confronted with his crimes, suggesting a man who has long since made peace with his dark duties. Though loyal to the Forsworn cause, years of orchestrating violence have left him somewhat world-weary, yet he continues his duties with grim determination.', 'A elderly Breton of average height with sharp, aristocratic features and a notably prominent nose. His advanced age is evident in his deeply lined face and thinning white hair, though he maintains an erect posture that suggests continued physical vitality. His hands show the smoothness of wealth rather than labor, though occasional scars hint at his more violent activities.', '* Madanach - King in Rags and supreme leader, whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Thonar Silver-Blood - Nominal employer and unwitting cover for Forsworn activities * Uaile - Trusted Forsworn servant and bodyguard * Tynan - Loyal Forsworn servant and house guard * Morven - Dedicated Forsworn servant and conspirator', 'Officially, Nepos serves as a administrator and problem-solver for the Silver-Blood family, managing worker relations and business affairs. Secretly, he operates as a high-ranking Forsworn agent, coordinating attacks and maintaining communication between Madanach and Forsworn operatives throughout the Reach.', '* Expert-level Illusion magic specializing in manipulation and fear spells * Accomplished Nightblade combining stealth and magic * Master of subterfuge and political maneuvering * Skilled administrator and negotiator * Proficient in dagger combat and assassination techniques', 'Speaks with refined, educated diction and a soft, measured tone that carries subtle authority. His manner of speech reflects his dual nature - cultured and diplomatic in public, but capable of delivering cold, direct threats when his true allegiance is revealed.', '* Advance the Forsworn cause through strategic violence and political manipulation * Maintain his cover as a respected citizen while serving Madanach''s interests * Eventually see the Reach returned to its native people * Ensure the continuation of Forsworn operations in Markarth after his eventual death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nerien', 'Nerien is a distinguished member of the enigmatic Psijic Order who serves as a mystical guide and herald of warning to the future Arch-Mage of the College of Winterhold. His ethereal appearances at crucial moments demonstrate both the Order''s ancient power to manipulate time and space, and their active interest in preventing catastrophic magical events in Skyrim.', 'highelf, mage, scholar, skyrimall, psijic', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Trained from a young age within the secretive halls of Artaeum, Nerien rose through the ranks of the Psijic Order through dedication to their esoteric magical practices and adherence to the Old Ways. His mastery of temporal magic and keen insight into possible futures led to his selection as an emissary to the outside world during times of great importance.', 'Nerien exhibits the characteristic reserve and formality of both his High Elven heritage and Psijic training, speaking with measured gravity about matters of great import. While maintaining professional distance, he shows genuine concern for the fate of Nirn and those who might protect it, demonstrating the Order''s philosophy of subtle guidance rather than direct intervention.', 'Tall and slender like most Altmer, Nerien possesses the golden skin and sharp features characteristic of his race. His face shows the weathering of centuries of magical study, with keen eyes that seem to peer through time itself.', '* Psijic Order - Loyal member and representative * Savos Aren - Professional awareness as Arch-Mage of the College * Ancano - Subject of observation and concern * The Last Dragonborn - Chosen recipient of warnings and guidance', 'As a senior member of the Psijic Order, Nerien serves as both a keeper of ancient magical knowledge and an observer of significant magical events. His role includes monitoring temporal anomalies and intervening through visions when necessary to prevent magical catastrophes.', '* Master of temporal magic and manipulation of time * Expert in telepathic communication and projection * Advanced knowledge of ancient magical artifacts and their potential dangers * Skilled in foreseeing possible future events and their consequences * Proficient in traditional Psijic magical practices', 'Nerien speaks with formal, measured tones befitting his ancient order, choosing words carefully and precisely. His dialogue carries gravitas and urgency while maintaining an air of mystical authority.', '* Guide worthy individuals to prevent magical catastrophes that threaten Nirn * Preserve the balance of magical forces in accordance with the Old Ways * Protect the secrets and traditions of the Psijic Order * Monitor and contain dangerous magical artifacts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nervous_patron', 'The Nervous Patron is a troubled Nord warrior who finds himself driven to perform the Black Sacrament, seeking the Dark Brotherhood''s services in Windhelm''s Candlehearth Hall. His anxious demeanor and desperate circumstances make him stand out among typical contract givers, suggesting a man pushed to his limits by whatever situation led him to seek an assassin''s services.', 'nord, warrior, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, he lived a relatively ordinary life until recent events forced him to consider darker solutions to his problems. Having learned of the Dark Brotherhood through whispered tales and a copy of ''A Kiss, Sweet Mother,'' he performed the Black Sacrament in secret, though the ritual''s disturbing nature clearly left him shaken. His possession of the ritual book suggests he may have been planning this course of action for some time, despite his evident discomfort with the whole process.', 'A naturally anxious and hesitant individual, the Nervous Patron exhibits clear signs of moral conflict over his decision to hire an assassin. His shakiness and uncertainty suggest someone unused to criminal dealings, yet desperate enough to overcome his reservations. Despite his evident fear, he shows determination in seeing his contract through, indicating the severity of whatever drove him to this point.', 'A typical Nord male with a somewhat slight build for his race, showing signs of stress and lack of sleep. His face bears the weathered features common to Windhelm''s residents, with notably dark circles under his eyes and a perpetually tense expression. His hands often tremble, and his posture is notably hunched, as if trying to make himself less visible.', '* Thoring - Innkeeper at Candlehearth Hall who provides him refuge * Contract Target - Unknown individual who has wronged him severely enough to warrant assassination * Dark Brotherhood - Temporary client relationship, marked by fear and desperate trust * Windhelm Guards - Keeps distance to avoid drawing attention to his activities', 'While his exact profession is unclear, his warrior classification and modest dress suggest he may be a former soldier or mercenary who has fallen on hard times. His current activities appear focused entirely on arranging and ensuring the completion of his dark contract.', '* Basic combat training typical of Nord warriors * Sufficient literacy to read and understand the Black Sacrament ritual * Knowledge of Dark Brotherhood contacts and protocols * Basic survival skills common to Windhelm residents', 'Speaks in a shaky, hesitant manner with frequent pauses and nervous glances around the room. His vocabulary is simple but proper, suggesting basic education, while his voice often drops to a whisper when discussing the contract.', '* Ensure the successful completion of his Dark Brotherhood contract * Avoid detection by authorities or others who might discover his actions * Return to a normal life once his target is eliminated * Find peace from whatever situation drove him to such desperate measures');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('niels', 'Niels was a seasoned Nord hunter and member of Valdr''s renowned hunting party operating out of Falkreath Hold. Known for his expertise in tracking dangerous prey, particularly bears, he met his end alongside fellow hunter Ari when their group encountered hostile spriggans in Moss Mother Cavern.', 'nord, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath Hold, Niels developed his hunting skills from an early age, learning to survive in the dense forests of his homeland. He eventually joined forces with Valdr''s hunting party, earning a reputation for tracking and taking down some of the most dangerous prey in the region, particularly bears whose pelts fetched excellent prices in the markets.', 'Niels was a pragmatic and stoic Nord who approached his dangerous profession with calculated precision rather than reckless bravado. Though not particularly sociable, he was loyal to his hunting companions and took pride in his tracking abilities, displaying the typical Nord trait of facing danger head-on without complaint.', 'Niels possessed the robust physique typical of Nord hunters, with well-developed muscles from years of tracking and fighting dangerous prey. His body bore numerous scars from close encounters with bears and other predators, testament to his dangerous profession.', '* Valdr - Respected leader of his hunting party and longtime companion * Ari - Fellow hunter and companion who died in the same incident * Falkreath merchants - Regular business contacts who purchased their pelts and animal products * Local trappers and hunters - Professional acquaintances who shared information about prey movements', 'Niels worked as a professional hunter specializing in tracking and hunting dangerous prey, particularly bears, whose pelts commanded high prices in the markets. As part of Valdr''s hunting party, he contributed to supplying Falkreath''s leather workers and fur traders with high-quality pelts and animal products.', '* Expert tracker with particular expertise in following bear trails * Proficient in light armor combat techniques suited for wilderness hunting * Skilled with one-handed weapons, particularly suited for close-quarter combat with dangerous prey * Advanced knowledge of wilderness survival and animal behavior patterns', 'Niels spoke in the gruff, direct manner typical of Nord hunters, favoring practical communication over unnecessary conversation. His vocabulary focused on hunting terminology and wilderness knowledge, delivered with a thick Nordic accent.', '* Build a reputation as one of Skyrim''s most skilled bear hunters * Accumulate enough wealth through hunting to potentially establish his own hunting lodge * Protect Falkreath''s territories from dangerous predators that threaten local settlements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nikulas', 'Nikulas was a brave Nord warrior from the Second Era who led a group of companions on a fateful quest to find Sovngarde. His journey was cut short by the betrayal of the wizard Grimkell, who turned him and two companions to stone, though they were eventually avenged and found their eternal rest in the Hall of Valor.', 'nord', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born in the Second Era, Nikulas grew up in the warrior culture of the Nords, developing a deep fascination with the legends of Sovngarde. He gathered a group of like-minded companions and embarked on a spiritual quest to find the Nordic afterlife, demonstrating remarkable leadership and determination. Their journey led them to Solstheim, where they encountered the treacherous wizard Grimkell, resulting in their petrification at Brodir Grove.', 'Nikulas embodies the archetypal Nordic warrior spirit - proud, honorable, and unflinching in the face of adversity. His leadership qualities are evident in his ability to inspire and unite his companions in pursuit of their shared goal. Even after death, he maintains his warrior''s dignity and shows no bitterness about his betrayal, instead focusing on the honor of finally reaching Sovngarde.', 'Nikulas possesses the typical robust build of a Nord warrior, with broad shoulders and strong features hardened by years of combat and harsh climate. His physical presence commands respect, reflecting his role as a leader and warrior. In death, his spirit maintains the proud bearing of his mortal form.', '* Erlendr - Fellow companion who shared his fate at Brodir Grove * Hunroor - Another companion turned to stone by Grimkell * Grimkell - Treacherous wizard who betrayed and petrified him * Ulfgar the Unending - Honored ally who avenged their deaths * Two unnamed companions - Fellow warriors on the quest to Sovngarde', 'In life, Nikulas served as a warrior and quest leader, guiding his companions on their spiritual journey to find Sovngarde. In death, he resides as an honored soul in the Hall of Valor, where he continues to embody the warrior spirit among the greatest Nordic heroes.', '* Exceptional leadership abilities and tactical combat expertise * Mastery of traditional Nordic combat techniques * Advanced knowledge of Nordic lore and traditions * Skilled navigator and pathfinder * Proficient in survival skills necessary for extended expeditions', 'Nikulas speaks with the direct, gruff manner typical of Nordic warriors, favoring straightforward statements over flowery language. His words carry the weight of authority and experience, reflecting his role as a leader and his warrior''s perspective on life and death.', '* Complete the spiritual journey to find Sovngarde * Lead his companions safely through their quest * Uphold Nordic traditions and warrior values * Achieve an honorable place among the heroes in the Hall of Valor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nils', 'Nils is a gruff, hardworking Nord who serves as both cook and caretaker at Candlehearth Hall in Windhelm, taking pride in his daily duties of wood chopping and meal preparation. Despite his advancing age, he maintains a strong work ethic and harbors a deep-seated resentment toward the Empire, reflecting the general sentiment of many Windhelm residents.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm during the pre-Great War era, Nils likely witnessed firsthand the deteriorating relations between the Empire and Skyrim. His experiences during and after the Great War shaped his anti-Imperial sentiments, leading him to eventually settle into a life of service at Candlehearth Hall, where his reliability and work ethic earned him consideration as Elda Early-Dawn''s potential successor.', 'Nils is a pragmatic and hardened individual who finds satisfaction in physical labor and routine. His gruff exterior and anti-Imperial sentiments mask a reliable and dedicated worker who takes pride in maintaining Windhelm''s oldest inn. Though not particularly sociable, he maintains a professional demeanor while handling his duties, even when dealing with non-Nord residents of the city.', 'Nils is an elderly Nord with the weathered features and sturdy build typical of his race, though age has begun to show in his lined face and graying hair. His years of physical labor have maintained his strength despite his advanced age, with calloused hands and a still-straight posture reflecting his active lifestyle.', '* Elda Early-Dawn - His employer and owner of Candlehearth Hall, who has mixed feelings about his capabilities * Revyn Sadri - Business contact who receives wood deliveries, though their relationship remains strictly professional * Oengul War-Anvil - Regular wood delivery recipient at the blacksmith * Local Nords - Generally respected member of the traditional Nord community', 'Nils serves as the cook and caretaker at Candlehearth Hall, with responsibilities including food preparation, wood chopping, and delivery services throughout Windhelm. He is considered the backup innkeeper should anything happen to Elda Early-Dawn, though she has expressed doubts about his ability to manage the establishment.', '* Experienced cook with knowledge of traditional Nord cuisine, author of ''Chaurus Pie: A Recipe'' * Proficient woodcutter with years of experience in lumber preparation * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Knowledge of inn maintenance and basic hospitality services', 'Nils speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with the thick accent common to Windhelm Nords. His speech is often terse and practical, focusing on work-related matters with little patience for idle conversation.', '* Maintain his position and reputation at Candlehearth Hall * Continue providing reliable service to Windhelm''s citizens despite his advancing age * Preserve traditional Nord ways in the face of Imperial influence * Potentially take over management of Candlehearth Hall if the opportunity arises');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nilsine_shatter-shield', 'Nilsine Shatter-Shield is a grieving Nord woman from one of Windhelm''s most prominent families, struggling with the recent murder of her twin sister Friga by a serial killer known as ''The Butcher.'' She maintains a daily routine visiting the market and religious sites while trying to balance honoring her sister''s memory with her father''s wishes to move forward with life.', 'nord, noble, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born into the wealthy and respected Shatter-Shield clan of Windhelm, Nilsine grew up privileged alongside her twin sister Friga. The sisters were inseparable until Friga''s tragic murder by a serial killer, an event that fundamentally changed Nilsine''s outlook on life and fractured several of her relationships, including her friendship with Muiri.', 'Nilsine is deeply melancholic and introspective, often dwelling on her sister''s death while struggling to maintain normalcy in her daily life. Though capable of occasional lighthearted moments, as seen in her market interactions, she carries a perpetual sadness that colors most of her interactions. She shows signs of survivor''s guilt and seems torn between honoring her sister''s memory and following her father''s wishes to move forward.', 'As a Nord woman, Nilsine has the characteristic fair complexion and strong features of her race. She bears a striking resemblance to her deceased twin sister Friga, with similar facial features that serve as a constant reminder to her family of their loss. Her bearing and posture reflect her upper-class upbringing despite her current emotional state.', '* Tova Shatter-Shield - Mother, sharing in grief over Friga''s death * Torbjorn Shatter-Shield - Father, pushing the family to move forward * Friga Shatter-Shield - Deceased twin sister, victim of ''The Butcher'' * Muiri - Former friend turned bitter enemy who wishes her dead * Hillevi Cruel-Sea - Friendly market acquaintance * Helgird - Priest she visits at the Hall of the Dead', 'As a member of the wealthy Shatter-Shield clan, Nilsine has no formal occupation but maintains the social obligations of her family''s high status. She represents her family''s interests in daily market interactions and maintains their social connections through regular visits to important city locations.', '* Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense * Social etiquette and upper-class manners * Market haggling and negotiation * Knowledge of Nord funeral rites and traditions', 'Nilsine speaks in a somber, reflective tone that often circles back to thoughts of her sister''s death. Her speech patterns reflect her upper-class upbringing, though tinged with melancholy, occasionally brightening during market interactions.', '* Find peace and balance between honoring Friga''s memory and moving forward with life * Maintain her family''s social standing in Windhelm despite their tragedy * Support her mother through their shared grief while respecting her father''s wishes * Avoid the fate that befell her sister while navigating a city with an active serial killer');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('niluva_hlaalu', 'Niluva Hlaalu is a fallen noble of the Great House Hlaalu who now works as a laborer at Black-Briar Meadery while struggling with a devastating skooma addiction. Despite her prestigious family background, she lives in poverty at Haelga''s Bunkhouse, caught in a cycle of substance abuse and mounting debts that threatens both her employment and housing.', 'darkelf, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Born into the once-powerful House Hlaalu of Morrowind, Niluva likely fled to Skyrim following her family''s fall from grace after the Argonian invasion. Her descent into skooma addiction presumably began as a way to cope with the trauma of displacement and loss of status, though she has been reluctant to share details of her past with others.', 'Defensive and quick-tempered, Niluva masks her shame and vulnerability behind a facade of hostility, particularly when confronted about her addiction. Though she expresses genuine desire to overcome her skooma dependency, her willpower is frequently overwhelmed by physical and psychological cravings, leading to a cycle of failed attempts at sobriety followed by relapse.', 'A slender Dunmer woman with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her race, showing signs of premature aging and poor health due to her skooma addiction. Her once-refined features bear the weathered look of someone who has fallen far from privilege, with dark circles under her eyes and trembling hands betraying her struggles with substance abuse.', '* Indaryn - Her supervisor at the meadery who threatens to fire her for poor performance * Haelga - Her landlord who grows increasingly impatient with late rent payments * Svana Far-Shield - Haelga''s niece who shows little sympathy for her situation * Romlyn Dreth - Coworker who understands her struggles and shows her kindness * House Hlaalu - Her estranged noble family in Morrowind', 'Niluva works as a laborer at Black-Briar Meadery, performing various tasks in the brewing and bottling process. Her position is precarious due to her addiction affecting her work performance, with her supervisor Indaryn frequently threatening termination.', '* Basic knowledge of meadery operations and brewing processes * Educated background with reading and writing abilities typical of Dunmer nobility * Survival skills developed from life on the streets * Understanding of skooma trade networks and illegal substance acquisition', 'She speaks with a mix of refined Dunmer pronunciation and rough street dialect, often punctuating her speech with defensive snaps and bitter commentary about her circumstances. Her voice frequently carries an edge of desperation and barely-contained anxiety.', '* Break free from skooma addiction and regain control of her life * Maintain her employment at the meadery and avoid eviction from the bunkhouse * Prove her worth to those who view her as worthless * Eventually restore her dignity and perhaps reconnect with her family');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nimphaneth', 'Nimphaneth is a Wood Elf cannibal who has found her true calling among the secret cult of Namira worshippers in Reachcliff Cave. She approaches her dark practices with an unsettling enthusiasm and genuine appreciation for what she considers a sacred culinary art, viewing cannibalism as both a spiritual calling and a refined taste.', 'woodelf, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, Nimphaneth likely grew up in a culture that already practiced ritual cannibalism through the Green Pact, making her transition to Namira worship natural. She made her way to Skyrim seeking like-minded individuals who would understand her particular tastes, eventually finding her way to Eola and the cult of Namira.', 'Nimphaneth is disturbingly cheerful about her cannibalistic practices, treating them as perfectly normal and even sophisticated. She shows no moral conflict about her activities, instead displaying an epicurean enthusiasm for human flesh that borders on connoisseurship. Her complete lack of remorse or hesitation suggests a deeply ingrained belief system that has fully normalized her dark appetites.', 'Like most Bosmer, Nimphaneth has a slight, athletic build with the characteristic pointed ears and angular features of her race. Her eyes hold an unsettling gleam of anticipation, and her teeth, though normal in appearance, are meticulously maintained - a detail that takes on a disturbing significance given her dietary preferences.', '* Eola - Fellow cultist and leader figure whom she deeply respects * Sanyon - Cave companion and fellow cannibal * Namira - Daedric Prince she worships through cannibalistic rituals * Other Cultists - Considers them refined dining companions and spiritual family', 'Nimphaneth serves as a dedicated member of Namira''s cult, participating in their ritualistic feasts and helping to maintain their hidden sanctuary. She likely acts as both a recruiter and procurer for the cult, using her cheerful demeanor to disarm potential victims or identify possible converts.', '* Experienced in preparing and preserving specific types of meat * Skilled in stealth and ambush techniques necessary for cult activities * Knowledgeable in Namira''s rites and rituals * Proficient in basic combat skills needed for hunting prey', 'Her speech is direct and enthusiastic, especially when discussing meals, with an unsettling cheerfulness that belies the horrific nature of her activities. She speaks with the refined vocabulary of a gourmand, albeit applied to cannibalistic pursuits.', '* Continue serving Namira through participation in ritual feasts * Perfect her culinary skills with human flesh * Help expand the cult''s influence in the Reach * Maintain the secrecy and security of their cave sanctuary');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nimriel', 'Nimriel is a dedicated Wood Elf farmer who transformed from a simple farmhand to the capable overseer of Pelagia Farm following the death of its original owner. Her quiet competence and agricultural expertise have earned her respect among Whiterun''s residents, proving that even in Skyrim''s harsh climate, Bosmer can excel beyond their traditional forest-dwelling roles.', 'woodelf, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, Nimriel migrated to Skyrim seeking opportunities beyond the rigid traditions of her homeland. She found employment at Pelagia Farm, where her natural affinity for working with plants helped her quickly master the challenges of farming in Skyrim''s harsh climate. After years of loyal service, she proved herself capable enough to take over operations when Severio Pelagia fell during the Battle for Whiterun.', 'Nimriel exhibits a humble and diligent nature, approaching her work with quiet determination and unwavering focus. Despite facing prejudice as a Bosmer in Nordic lands, she maintains an optimistic outlook and lets her work ethic speak for itself. She shows particular pride in maintaining the farm''s productivity while staying true to her Bosmer values of respecting the natural world.', 'Nimriel has the typical slight, athletic build of a Wood Elf, standing shorter than most races but moving with natural grace. Her skin has a healthy tan from constant outdoor work, while her features show the characteristic sharp angles of her race. Her hands are callused from farm work, but she maintains the natural agility common to her people.', '* Severio Pelagia (Deceased) - Former employer who trusted her with increasing responsibility * Carlotta Valentia - Fellow food vendor with whom she trades goods and farming advice * Whiterun Guards - Maintain a protective watch over the farm since it provides food for the city * Local farmers - Respectful professional relationships with other agricultural workers in the area', 'Nimriel serves as the de facto owner and operator of Pelagia Farm, managing all aspects of crop cultivation and harvest. She oversees the farm''s daily operations, including planting, maintenance, and selling produce to Whiterun''s merchants and citizens. Her position is crucial to Whiterun''s food supply, especially during times of conflict.', '* Expert farmer with deep knowledge of crop rotation and soil management * Skilled herbalist able to identify and cultivate various plants * Proficient in basic archery, maintaining traditional Bosmer hunting skills * Natural agility and dexterity typical of Wood Elves * Basic business acumen developed through managing farm operations', 'Nimriel speaks in a soft, measured tone, using simple but precise language that reflects her practical nature. Her accent carries subtle hints of her Valenwood origins, though years in Skyrim have given her speech patterns a slight Nordic influence.', '* Maintain and expand Pelagia Farm''s productivity to honor Severio''s memory * Prove that Bosmer can excel in agricultural roles despite their traditional hunter-gatherer background * Eventually own the farm outright rather than serving as its caretaker * Create a sustainable farming model that balances productivity with respect for nature');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('niranye', 'Niranye is a sophisticated Altmer merchant who has masterfully adapted to life in the harsh Nordic city of Windhelm, balancing a respectable public trading business with covert criminal connections. Despite the city''s notorious prejudice against elves, she has carved out a successful niche through careful networking and shrewd business acumen.', 'highelf, merchant, blacksmith, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally from the Summerset Isles, Niranye established herself in Windhelm during a period of significant opportunity in Skyrim. She previously maintained connections with the Thieves Guild during their golden age, serving as a fence before their decline. Through careful manipulation of social connections and demonstration of her usefulness to the local community, she overcame the typical Nordic prejudice against elves to establish a legitimate business.', 'Pragmatic and shrewd, Niranye embodies the cunning adaptability often associated with her Altmer heritage. She maintains a carefully cultivated public persona of respectability while secretly engaging in criminal enterprise, displaying remarkable social intelligence in navigating Windhelm''s prejudiced environment. Unlike the struggling Dunmer population, she takes pride in having overcome racial barriers through careful manipulation of the system rather than direct confrontation.', 'Niranye possesses the typical golden-skinned, tall, and slender physique characteristic of High Elves. Her features are sharp and elegant, with the distinctive pointed ears and high cheekbones of her race. She maintains an immaculate appearance befitting a successful merchant, showing signs of middle age by Altmer standards.', '* Thieves Guild - Former and potentially renewed business associate * Summerset Shadows - Complicated relationship as potential rival fence * Local Nord Community - Carefully maintained business relationships * Dunmer Community - Distant and somewhat dismissive attitude * Torbjorn Shatter-Shield - Business acquaintance in Windhelm', 'Niranye operates a successful market stall in Windhelm''s Stone Quarter, dealing in general goods and potentially serving as a fence for stolen merchandise. She maintains a careful balance between legitimate trade and underground connections, operating her stall during regular business hours while conducting more discrete transactions after hours.', '* Expert merchant with keen understanding of value and trade * Accomplished fence for stolen goods * Skilled negotiator and social manipulator * Proficient in basic combat with daggers * Expert at maintaining dual identities and secret operations', 'Niranye speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary typical of educated Altmer, but can adjust her tone to be more approachable when dealing with Nordic customers. She maintains a professional demeanor in public while being more direct and cunning in private conversations.', '* Maintain and expand her legitimate business empire in Windhelm * Reestablish profitable connections with the Thieves Guild * Continue to navigate and exploit Windhelm''s social hierarchy * Accumulate wealth and influence while maintaining a respectable facade');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('niruin', 'Niruin is a former wealthy Valenwood wine merchant who abandoned his comfortable life to join the Thieves Guild in pursuit of excitement and adventure. As the Guild''s master archery trainer, he combines his natural Bosmer talents with years of experience to teach others while maintaining a surprisingly laid-back lifestyle within the organization.', 'woodelf, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born into a carpenter''s family in Valenwood, Niruin rejected his father''s trade to become a successful wine merchant, amassing considerable wealth through his business acumen. Despite his financial success, he found himself unfulfilled by the merchant''s life and eventually made his way to Skyrim, where he joined the Thieves Guild seeking thrill and adventure. His transition from legitimate businessman to skilled thief was remarkably smooth, aided by his natural Bosmer abilities and social connections established through his merchant past.', 'Niruin exhibits a notably relaxed and easy-going demeanor that belies his criminal profession, often approaching situations with a casual confidence born from his privileged background. He maintains a shrewd business sense from his merchant days while embracing the excitement of thievery, though his actual daily routine suggests he prefers comfort over constant adventure. Despite his wealthy upbringing, he shows no signs of snobbery, instead taking pride in his current role and forming genuine connections with his fellow guild members.', 'As a Bosmer, Niruin possesses the characteristic slight build and agile frame typical of his race, with the pointed ears and angular features common to mer. His years of archery practice have given him well-developed arm and shoulder muscles, while his merchant background is reflected in his good posture and well-groomed appearance.', '* Thieves Guild Members - Generally positive relationships with fellow members, particularly those who respect his archery expertise * Mercer Frey - Professional relationship as Guildmaster, though later turns antagonistic after Mercer''s betrayal * Brynjolf - Respects his leadership and judgment within the Guild * Family in Valenwood - Distant relationship with his carpenter father, whom he chose not to follow * Maven Black-Briar - Business connection through his knowledge of wines and Guild activities', 'Niruin serves as the master archery trainer for the Thieves Guild, offering his expertise to both guild members and the Dragonborn. He maintains a position of respect within the guild hierarchy, combining his criminal activities with his role as an instructor while participating in various guild operations.', '* Master-level archery skills with exceptional accuracy and technique * Expert in stealth and criminal techniques * Professional-level knowledge of wines and merchant trade * Skilled in lockpicking and infiltration * Natural Bosmer abilities including command of animals and resistance to disease and poison', 'Niruin speaks in a relaxed, confident manner with occasional references to his past life as a wine merchant, often using sophisticated vocabulary that reflects his educated background. His tone is generally friendly and casual, though he can adopt a more serious demeanor when discussing business or training.', '* Maintain his comfortable position within the Thieves Guild while enjoying the excitement of criminal life * Continue developing his archery skills and passing knowledge to others * Build his reputation as one of Skyrim''s premier archery trainers * Accumulate wealth through both legitimate training and illegitimate activities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nirya', 'Nirya is an ambitious and politically-minded High Elf sorceress at the College of Winterhold who constantly schemes to advance her position within the institution. She maintains a bitter rivalry with fellow mage Faralda while engaging in a secret romance with Sergius Turrianus, demonstrating her complex web of personal and professional relationships within the College.', 'highelf, scholar, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_femaleelfhaughty', '', 'Born and educated in the Summerset Isles, Nirya made her way to Skyrim seeking greater magical knowledge and political opportunity at the College of Winterhold. Her natural talent for magic combined with her ruthless ambition helped her secure a position as a scholar, though her focus on political maneuvering often overshadows her academic pursuits.', 'Nirya is calculating, paranoid, and deeply competitive, particularly regarding her rivalry with Faralda. She maintains a facade of superiority and confidence while harboring deep insecurities about her position within the College. Her ambitious nature leads her to constantly seek advantages over others, even at the cost of genuine relationships.', 'Tall and slender like most Altmer, Nirya carries herself with practiced poise and grace. Her features are sharp and angular, typical of her race, and she maintains an appearance of pristine elegance even in the harsh climate of Winterhold.', '* Faralda - Bitter rival and fellow College member whom she actively tries to undermine * Sergius Turrianus - Secret lover and source of political information, though their relationship may be manipulative * College Members - Generally maintains professional but distant relationships * Arch-Mage - Shows excessive deference when speaking to them, especially after player assumes the role', 'Nirya serves as a scholar at the College of Winterhold, focusing primarily on Destruction magic. While she holds no official teaching position, she maintains influence through political maneuvering and careful cultivation of relationships with key College members.', '* Advanced practitioner of Destruction magic * Skilled political manipulator and information gatherer * Competent researcher and academic * Expert in magical theory and application * Adept at maintaining multiple personas and relationships for personal gain', 'Nirya speaks with a haughty, sophisticated accent typical of High Elves, often employing passive-aggressive undertones and veiled threats. Her speech patterns reveal both her educated background and her tendency toward paranoia and manipulation.', '* Advance to a leadership position within the College of Winterhold * Discredit and remove Faralda as a rival for influence * Maintain her secret relationship with Sergius while using it for political advantage * Increase her personal power and influence within the magical community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nivenor', 'Nivenor is a wealthy, self-indulgent Wood Elf living in Riften who openly disdains her husband Bolli''s charitable endeavors. She represents the materialistic side of Riften''s society, pursuing a life of luxury and pleasure while maintaining a reputation for infidelity.', 'woodelf, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Originally drawn to Riften''s opportunities for wealth and comfort, Nivenor married Bolli, the owner of Riften Fishery, primarily for his financial status. Her marriage appears to have been one of convenience rather than love, as evidenced by her numerous affairs and disdain for her husband''s charitable activities.', 'Nivenor is materialistic, hedonistic, and openly disdainful of both poverty and charity. She displays narcissistic tendencies, showing little empathy for others while maintaining a sense of entitlement to luxury and comfort. Her flirtatious nature and unfaithfulness suggest she values immediate gratification over lasting relationships.', 'As a Wood Elf, Nivenor possesses the characteristic elven features including pointed ears and almond-shaped eyes. She maintains an elegant appearance befitting her wealthy status, with well-groomed hair and a practiced posture that conveys her self-importance.', '* Bolli - Her husband, whom she views with contempt due to his charitable nature * Various Male Lovers - Multiple implied romantic encounters throughout Riften * Haelga - Possible rival, as Bolli has had affairs with her * Riften Merchants - Regular business relationships due to her shopping habits * Maven Black-Briar - Likely social acquaintance due to their shared upper-class status', 'Nivenor holds a ceremonial position at the Riften Fishery, where she performs minimal administrative duties for a few hours each day. Her primary occupation appears to be that of a wealthy housewife, spending most of her time shopping and pursuing personal interests.', '* Basic business administration and bookkeeping for the fishery * Social manipulation and seduction * Bargaining and mercantile abilities * Basic combat with daggers for self-defense', 'She speaks with a condescending, dismissive tone, often using cutting remarks and sarcasm. Her vocabulary and manner of speaking reflect her upper-class pretensions, particularly when addressing those she considers beneath her station.', '* Maintain and increase her access to luxury and wealth * Prevent her husband from giving away their fortune to charity * Pursue personal pleasure and entertainment regardless of social consequences * Secure her position in Riften''s upper society');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('niyya', 'Niyya is a Redguard sorceress who survived horrific imprisonment and experimentation at the hands of the vengeful Ildari Sarothril. Originally part of a mining group that showed mercy to an injured stranger, she became the last surviving victim of Ildari''s cruel betrayal and magical experiments.', 'redguard, mage, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Niyya was part of a mining crew working in Solstheim when they discovered a gravely wounded Ildari Sarothril. After the group nursed Ildari back to health, she betrayed them in a night attack, killing most and imprisoning the survivors for twisted magical experiments. Niyya endured prolonged captivity and witnessed the deaths of her fellow prisoners until becoming the last survivor.', 'Despite her traumatic experiences, Niyya demonstrates remarkable resilience and a compassionate nature, as shown by her group''s initial decision to help Ildari. Her time in captivity has left her frightened and desperate, with a deep-seated desire to escape Solstheim and the memories of her ordeal. She carries emotional scars from witnessing the deaths of her companions.', 'As a Redguard, Niyya has dark skin and the characteristic athletic build of her race. Her time in captivity has left her somewhat gaunt and weathered, though she retains the natural grace common to magic practitioners.', '* Former Mining Crew - Deceased companions who were killed or experimented on by Ildari * Ildari Sarothril - Former patient turned torturer and mortal enemy * Geldis Sadri - Owner of The Retching Netch who provides her sanctuary after escape', 'Originally a mining crew member with magical abilities, suggesting she combined physical labor with magical expertise. After her rescue, she becomes a refugee at The Retching Netch, occasionally helping to spread temple propaganda to earn her keep.', '* Competent in sorcery, particularly evident by her designation as a sorceress * Mining and excavation experience from her previous work * Survival skills developed during imprisonment * Basic knowledge of healing, learned from helping nurse Ildari', 'Speaks rapidly and urgently when first encountered, with fear evident in her voice. After rescue, her speech remains anxious but becomes more measured, though still carrying undertones of trauma.', '* Escape Solstheim and reach the mainland to start a new life * Process and recover from her traumatic experiences * Find a safe place to rebuild her life away from dark memories');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('njada_stonearm', 'Njada Stonearm is a hardened Nord warrior and expert shield-bearer within the prestigious Companions of Whiterun. Known for her stern demeanor and exceptional blocking skills, she serves as both a combatant and instructor, embodying the warrior spirit of her organization while maintaining a notably defensive combat philosophy.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, companions, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Njada developed her distinctive fighting style through years of rigorous training and real-world combat experience. Her expertise in shield techniques likely stems from surviving numerous battles where defensive prowess proved more valuable than offensive might, eventually leading her to join the Companions where her skills earned her a position as a respected member and trainer.', 'Njada is characterized by her harsh, dismissive attitude and strong sense of pride in the Companions'' traditions. She''s particularly skeptical of newcomers and maintains a stern, almost hostile demeanor until they prove their worth through actions rather than words. Despite her rough exterior, she shows unwavering loyalty to the Companions and takes her role as a trainer seriously.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with a warrior''s physique, bearing the scars and calluses of countless battles. Her face carries a perpetual stern expression, with sharp features typical of her Nordic heritage and eyes that seem to constantly evaluate potential threats.', '* The Circle - Respects their authority but maintains professional distance * Athis - Frequent sparring partner and rival * Other Companions - Professional but somewhat distant relationships * New recruits - Shows initial disdain and skepticism * Skjor - Respected him as a worthy training partner before his death', 'Njada serves as both a warrior and trainer within the Companions, specializing in teaching blocking techniques to fellow members. She maintains her position as an expert-level trainer in block, capable of training others up to level 75 in this skill, while also participating in the organization''s various combat missions and contracts.', '* Master-level expertise in blocking and shield techniques * Proficient in one-handed combat, particularly with swords * Skilled in heavy armor usage and defensive tactics * Competent archer with hunting bow capabilities * Advanced understanding of combat strategy and defensive positioning', 'Njada speaks in a direct, often confrontational manner, frequently using dismissive or sarcastic tones. Her responses tend to be short and sharp, reflecting her no-nonsense attitude and general disdain for those she considers beneath her skill level.', '* Maintain and uphold the warrior traditions of the Companions * Perfect her mastery of defensive combat techniques * Prove herself worthy of greater recognition within the Companions * Train worthy warriors in the art of shield combat * Preserve the honor and legacy of the Companions through strict adherence to their ways');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nobleman', 'A refined and wealthy individual who exemplifies the upper echelons of Skyrim society, frequently found in the most prestigious districts of major cities like Solitude. Though born into privilege, they maintain their status through careful social networking and business acumen, representing the sophisticated elite class that exists above the common merchants and craftsmen.', 'noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born into one of Skyrim''s established noble families, they received extensive education in economics, politics, and proper etiquette from an early age. Their family''s wealth was built over generations through strategic land ownership and trade investments, particularly in the East Empire Company. They survived the Great War with their fortune largely intact by carefully maintaining neutrality while providing financial support to both sides.', 'Sophisticated and somewhat pretentious, they take great pride in their refined tastes and social status. While generally cordial to other members of the nobility, they tend to be dismissive of common folk unless they prove useful to their interests. They mask their shrewd business sense behind a facade of leisure and luxury.', 'Well-groomed and carrying themselves with practiced poise, they maintain a carefully manicured appearance befitting their station. Their hands are soft and unmarked by manual labor, while their complexion shows signs of regular access to the finest skincare products available in Skyrim. Their body shows the slight softness that comes from a life of comfort and rich foods.', '* East Empire Company - Major trading partner and source of steady income * Erikur - Fellow noble and business associate in Solitude * Vittoria Vici - Important social connection for Imperial trade dealings * Local Jarls - Maintains cordial relationships to protect business interests * Common merchants - Viewed as useful but socially inferior contacts', 'As a nobleman, they manage various business interests and property holdings while maintaining their social standing through regular participation in high society events. They serve on several merchant councils and occasionally act as an advisor to the Jarl on matters of commerce and trade.', '* Expert in business negotiations and contract law * Highly knowledgeable about wine, fine dining, and proper etiquette * Skilled at political maneuvering and social networking * Proficient in economics and trade logistics * Basic skill with a dress sword for ceremonial purposes', 'Speaks in a refined, measured tone with careful enunciation and frequent references to luxury goods or high society events. Their vocabulary is extensive and formal, often using flowery language to demonstrate their education and status.', '* Maintain and expand their family''s wealth and influence in Skyrim * Secure advantageous trade agreements with the East Empire Company * Establish stronger connections with the Imperial nobility * Navigate the civil war while protecting their assets and social position');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('noblewoman', 'A cultured Nord noblewoman who moves in Skyrim''s highest social circles and attends private gatherings with Emperor Titus Mede II. She represents the concerned voice of Skyrim''s nobility during a period of growing political instability and violence, while maintaining the refined demeanor expected of her station.', 'nord, noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born into one of Skyrim''s prominent noble families, she received extensive education in etiquette, politics, and the arts befitting her social status. She has likely spent significant time in both Skyrim''s courts and the Imperial City, developing connections with other members of the nobility and gaining intimate knowledge of political affairs.', 'Cautious and politically astute, she shows genuine concern for the stability of the Empire while maintaining diplomatic tact. Her refined manners mask a sharp mind that picks up on concerning patterns in recent events, though she''s careful to voice her worries in a way that doesn''t challenge authority directly.', 'A well-groomed Nord woman of middle age, carrying herself with the practiced poise of nobility. Her features reflect her Nord heritage but have been softened by a life of comfort, lacking the weathered quality common to many of her race.', '* Emperor Titus Mede II - Social acquaintance through noble circles * Fellow Noblemen - Regular social peers at political gatherings * Vittoria Vici - Former social connection whose murder deeply troubled her * Skyrim Noble Houses - Various family and political connections', 'Member of Skyrim''s nobility, likely managing family estates and engaging in political social circles. Her presence at the Emperor''s private dinner suggests she holds significant social standing among the province''s elite.', '* Expert knowledge of noble etiquette and political protocol * Educated in history, politics, and arts * Skilled at social navigation and diplomatic conversation * Management of estate affairs and household administration', 'She speaks in refined, measured tones with careful word choice and proper Imperial diction, despite her Nord heritage. Her vocabulary and delivery reflect her educated background while maintaining appropriate deference to those of higher station.', '* Maintain her family''s social position and influence in Skyrim''s noble circles * Preserve stability and order in the province during troubled times * Protect her interests and those of her peers from growing political violence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nocturnal', 'Nocturnal is the enigmatic Daedric Prince of darkness, luck, and night who serves as the patron deity of thieves across Tamriel. She maintains a complex relationship with the mortal realm through the Thieves Guild and her devoted Nightingales, granting subtle luck and fortune in exchange for service and devotion both in life and death.', 'daedric', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Nocturnal''s origins stretch back to the dawn of creation as one of the original et''Ada, the primordial beings who helped shape Nirn. She established her realm of Evergloam and created the Twilight Sepulcher as her primary point of influence on the mortal plane, instituting the Nightingales as her sworn protectors and choosing to work through subtle manipulation of luck rather than direct intervention.', 'Nocturnal is mysterious and aloof, displaying an air of otherworldly detachment in her rare interactions with mortals. She operates on an inscrutable agenda, granting her favor seemingly at whim while demanding absolute loyalty from her servants, though the true nature of her motivations remains unknown even to her most devoted followers. Her demeanor is simultaneously alluring and threatening, befitting her role as a being who deals in both fortune and misfortune.', 'Nocturnal manifests as a tall, regal female figure with pale skin and dark features that seem to absorb surrounding light. Her physical form radiates an aura of darkness and mystery, with eyes that gleam with ancient knowledge and power.', '* The Nightingales - Sworn protectors who serve as her agents in both life and death * Thieves Guild - Organization under her patronage and influence * Karliah - Loyal Nightingale who helped restore her influence * Gallus Desidenius - Former Nightingale who served faithfully until his murder * Mercer Frey - Treacherous Nightingale who stole the Skeleton Key', 'As a Daedric Prince, Nocturnal rules over her realm of Evergloam and maintains influence over darkness, luck, and night. She oversees the cosmic balance of fortune and misfortune, particularly as it relates to thieves and those who operate in shadow.', '* Absolute control over darkness and shadow * Ability to manipulate probability and luck * Power to grant supernatural abilities to her Nightingales * Command over her realm of Evergloam * Capacity to influence events through subtle means', 'Nocturnal speaks in formal, archaic tones with a voice that seems to echo from the void itself. Her words are often cryptic and layered with multiple meanings, delivered with regal authority and subtle condescension toward mortals.', '* Maintain her influence over the mortal realm through the Twilight Sepulcher * Secure eternal servants through the Nightingale Contract * Preserve the cosmic balance of fortune and misfortune * Expand her influence through the success of the Thieves Guild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('northwatch_guard', 'A stern and authoritative Thalmor guard stationed at Northwatch Keep, tasked with maintaining security and secrecy at this controversial detention facility. He represents the unwavering authority and superiority complex of the Thalmor, serving as the first line of defense against unwanted interference in their covert operations.', 'highelf, haafingar, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Recruited and thoroughly indoctrinated into the Thalmor''s ideology of Altmer supremacy from a young age, he earned his position through demonstrating absolute loyalty and strict adherence to protocol. His assignment to Northwatch Keep indicates both his reliability in maintaining secrecy and his willingness to participate in the Thalmor''s more controversial activities without question.', 'Rigid and bureaucratic, he embodies the cold efficiency and racial superiority typical of Thalmor operatives. Shows complete devotion to authority and chain of command, only yielding when presented with proper documentation from recognized superior powers like the Imperial Legion. Demonstrates no empathy for prisoners or their families, viewing them merely as objects of Thalmor interest.', 'Tall and lean like most High Elves, with the characteristic golden skin and sharp, angular features of his race. Carries himself with the rigid posture of a disciplined soldier, his face often set in a stern, disapproving expression that reflects his disdain for non-Altmer races.', '* Thalmor Leadership - Unwavering loyalty and obedience * Fellow Northwatch Guards - Professional working relationship based on shared duty * Imperial Legion - Reluctant recognition of their authority in certain matters * Prisoners - Views them as beneath his concern, merely objects of Thalmor interest * Local Nords - Contempt and disdain, particularly for those who question Thalmor authority', 'Serves as a security officer at Northwatch Keep, responsible for preventing unauthorized access and maintaining the secrecy of Thalmor operations. His duties include screening visitors, enforcing access restrictions, and ensuring no information about the facility''s activities reaches the public.', '* Trained in standard Thalmor combat techniques and security protocols * Proficient in intimidation and crowd control * Experienced in prisoner handling and facility security procedures * Basic knowledge of Imperial bureaucracy and documentation * Skilled in detecting deception and unauthorized entry attempts', 'Speaks in clipped, authoritative tones with a clear Altmer accent, favoring formal language that emphasizes his position of authority. His communication is direct and dismissive, designed to intimidate and discourage further inquiry.', '* Maintain absolute security and secrecy at Northwatch Keep * Advance within the Thalmor hierarchy through demonstrated loyalty and efficiency * Support the Thalmor''s greater mission of Altmer supremacy in Skyrim * Prevent any unauthorized access or information leaks about prisoner operations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('northwatch_interrogator', 'A sadistic High Elf interrogator stationed at Northwatch Keep who serves the Thalmor with unwavering dedication and cruel efficiency. His expertise in torture and information extraction makes him one of the most feared operatives within the keep''s dungeons, where he employs both physical and psychological methods to break his victims.', 'highelf, haafingar, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Trained from a young age in the art of interrogation by the Thalmor''s most experienced torturers, he rose through their ranks due to his exceptional ability to extract information from even the most resilient prisoners. His natural talent for causing pain, combined with his deep-seated belief in Altmer superiority, made him the perfect candidate for his current position at Northwatch Keep, where he has served for over a decade perfecting his brutal craft.', 'Cold, calculating, and utterly devoid of empathy, he takes genuine pleasure in the suffering of others, particularly non-mer races. His unwavering loyalty to the Thalmor and belief in Altmer supremacy drives him to perform his duties with zealous enthusiasm, viewing his work not just as a job but as a sacred duty to purge inferior races of their defiance.', 'Tall and lean even by Altmer standards, with sharp, angular features and cold, calculating eyes that seem to pierce through his victims. His hands are long and elegant despite the brutality they inflict, and his posture remains impeccably straight, reflecting his sense of racial superiority.', '* Thalmor Leadership - Loyal servant and valued asset for information extraction * Fellow Northwatch Guards - Professional relationships maintained through mutual dedication to the cause * Elenwen - Reports findings of significance to the First Emissary * Prisoners - Views them as lesser beings worthy only of suffering until they reveal useful information', 'Senior Interrogator at Northwatch Keep, responsible for extracting information from prisoners deemed valuable to Thalmor interests. He oversees the torture chamber and maintains detailed records of his interrogations, developing new methods of breaking both body and spirit.', '* Master of physical torture techniques utilizing both traditional and magical methods * Expert in psychological manipulation and breaking mental resistance * Skilled in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells for interrogation * Proficient in Restoration magic to keep prisoners alive for extended questioning * Experienced in alchemical creation of pain-inducing and truth-compelling potions', 'Speaks in a measured, aristocratic tone with precise diction and careful word choice, often employing cold sarcasm and subtle threats. His voice carries an underlying current of sadistic pleasure when addressing prisoners, though remains professionally detached when speaking with fellow Thalmor.', '* Advance within the Thalmor hierarchy through successful information extraction * Perfect new methods of interrogation that combine magical and physical torture * Prove the superiority of Altmer interrogation techniques over other methods * Root out all remaining Talos worship through careful questioning of captured worshippers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thalmor', 'The Thalmor are highly-trained Altmer agents serving as the militant governing force of the Third Aldmeri Dominion, combining religious zealotry with political ambition. They operate as enforcers, spies, and diplomats across Tamriel, particularly focused on suppressing Talos worship and asserting Mer superiority over the races of Men.', 'highelf, skyrimall, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Rising to power in the Summerset Isles after claiming credit for resolving the Oblivion Crisis, the Thalmor transformed from a fringe political faction into the ruling power of the Aldmeri Dominion. They launched the Great War against the Empire in 4E 171, resulting in the White-Gold Concordat that granted them significant authority across Imperial provinces, including Skyrim.', 'Thalmor agents are characterized by their extreme racial supremacist views and unwavering belief in Altmer superiority. They display cold efficiency, religious fanaticism, and often cruel dedication to their cause, showing little mercy to those who oppose them or violate their laws. Their arrogance and sense of cultural superiority typically manifests in condescending behavior toward other races.', 'Thalmor agents are tall, golden-skinned Altmer with the characteristic pointed ears and angular features of their race. They typically stand around 6''5" to 7'' tall with slender', 'athletic builds maintained through rigorous training. Their faces often bear stern', 'hawkish expressions reflecting their supremacist mindset."', '* Empire - Tense alliance maintained through the White-Gold Concordat * Stormcloaks - Active enemies due to their worship of Talos and rebellion * Blades - Sworn enemies hunted nearly to extinction * College of Winterhold - Suspicious monitoring of magical activities * Dark Elves - Strained relations despite shared elven heritage * Wood Elves - Subjugated allies within the Aldmeri Dominion', 'The Thalmor serve as the military, diplomatic, and law enforcement arm of the Aldmeri Dominion. Their duties include enforcing the ban on Talos worship, conducting intelligence operations, maintaining diplomatic relations, and eliminating threats to Dominion interests. They operate from their Embassy near Solitude and maintain various outposts across Skyrim.', 'Thalmor agents speak with cultured, upper-class accents and employ formal, sophisticated vocabulary that often carries condescending undertones. Their speech is characterized by careful word choice and subtle threats veiled behind diplomatic courtesy.');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('northwatch_prisoner', 'A weary prisoner held captive in the notorious Northwatch Keep by the Thalmor, suspected of worshipping Talos or supporting the Stormcloak rebellion. Their imprisonment represents the broader persecution of Nord culture and religious freedom under the White-Gold Concordat.', 'peasant', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally a common Nord farmer from the rural regions of Skyrim who was arrested by Thalmor justiciars on suspicion of Talos worship. Prior to their arrest, they lived a simple life tending crops and maintaining a small homestead, possibly in the Pale or Winterhold regions where Thalmor presence is particularly oppressive.', 'Broken in spirit but clinging to hope, the prisoner exhibits signs of severe psychological trauma from Thalmor interrogation and confinement. Despite their desperate situation, they maintain a quiet dignity and their Nordic cultural identity, though fear has made them hesitant to trust even potential rescuers.', 'A gaunt Nord with sunken eyes and pallid skin from extended imprisonment underground. Their once-sturdy farmer''s frame shows clear signs of malnourishment and muscle atrophy from confinement, with visible bruising and scars from Thalmor interrogation sessions.', '* Thalmor Guards - Cruel captors who regularly conduct interrogations * Fellow Prisoners - Shared suffering creates a silent bond, though interaction is limited * Family Members - Likely worried relatives somewhere in Skyrim, possibly searching for their missing kin * Thorald Gray-Mane - Fellow prisoner whose presence confirms the political nature of their imprisonment', 'Former farmer turned prisoner of the Thalmor, stripped of all status and possessions. Their days are spent enduring interrogations and attempting to maintain sanity in the harsh conditions of Northwatch Keep.', '* Basic agricultural knowledge from previous farming life * Fundamental survival skills common to Nordic culture * Physical endurance developed through farm work, though diminished by imprisonment * Basic understanding of Nordic traditions and customs', 'Speaks in short, desperate phrases with a hoarse voice from disuse and screaming during interrogations. Their words carry the distinct accent of a rural Nord, though fear makes them hesitant to say much.', '* Escape from Northwatch Keep and regain freedom * Survive the brutal conditions and Thalmor interrogations * Return to family and former life if possible * Avoid future Thalmor attention and persecution');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('noster_eagle-eye', 'Noster Eagle-Eye is a fallen Imperial war veteran whose life was forever changed during the Battle of Anvil in the Great War, where he lost both his eye and his dignity. Once a proud soldier, he now survives as a beggar in Solitude, carrying deep knowledge of warfare and wilderness survival despite his reduced circumstances.', 'imperial, archer, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Noster served with distinction in the Imperial Legion during the Great War against the Aldmeri Dominion. During the brutal Battle of Anvil, he sustained a grievous injury that cost him his eye, and was abandoned by his fellow soldiers who left him for dead. After fighting his way back home, his injuries prevented him from maintaining regular employment, eventually leading him to seek refuge in Solitude.', 'Despite his current circumstances, Noster maintains a complex mix of pride in his military service and bitter resignation about his fate. He shows remarkable resilience and willingness to share his knowledge with those who show him kindness, though years of begging have left him with a weary, defeated demeanor. His occasional references to his military past reveal glimpses of the proud soldier he once was.', 'A weathered Imperial man of middle age, with his most distinctive feature being the missing eye that earned him his surname. His body bears numerous scars from his military service, and years of living on the streets have left him with a gaunt, hardened appearance. Despite his circumstances, he maintains a soldier''s posture when standing.', '* Imperial Legion - Former brothers-in-arms who abandoned him at Anvil * Solitude Guards - Maintain a respectful distance due to his veteran status * Radiant Raiment Staff - Tolerates his presence outside their shop * Angeline Morrard - Shows occasional kindness, allowing him to beg near her shop * General Tullius - Represents the military structure that both defined and betrayed him', 'Noster survives as a beggar in Solitude, primarily stationed outside Radiant Raiment. Despite his reduced circumstances, he occasionally serves as an informal mentor to travelers, sharing his extensive knowledge of wilderness survival when shown kindness.', '* Expert in wilderness survival and navigation * Trained military tactician from his Legion service * Experienced in combat from his time in the Great War * Skilled at reading people and determining their intentions * Adept at surviving in urban environments despite limited resources', 'Speaks with a weary, defeated tone that occasionally gives way to flashes of military precision when discussing his past. His vocabulary reveals his educated military background, though his delivery is now colored by years of hardship and street life.', '* Recover his lost helmet, a symbol of his former glory and military service * Maintain his dignity despite his circumstances as a beggar * Share his knowledge and experience with those who show him respect * Find some measure of peace with his past and the betrayal he experienced');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nura_snow-shod', 'Nura Snow-Shod is a devoted priestess of Talos in Riften who maintains unwavering faith despite Imperial persecution. A grieving mother who lost her daughter to the civil war, she channels her pain and conviction into tending Talos'' shrine and preserving Nord religious traditions.', 'nord, priest, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Riften, Nura dedicated her life to Talos worship and became a respected priestess and healer. She trained her daughter Lilija to follow in her footsteps, but lost her to the civil war when Lilija joined the Stormcloaks as a healer and was killed in battle, her body never recovered due to Imperial burning of the dead.', 'Deeply pious and traditional, Nura maintains a dignified demeanor befitting her religious position. While warm to those who share her faith, she harbors deep resentment toward the Empire for banning Talos worship and indirectly causing her daughter''s death. Her grief manifests as increased religious devotion and support for Skyrim''s independence.', 'A mature Nord woman with the weathered features typical of her race, carrying herself with dignified bearing appropriate to her religious role. Her face shows signs of grief and long hours of prayer, yet maintains an aura of maternal warmth.', '* Vulwulf Snow-Shod - Beloved husband who shares her anti-Imperial sentiments * Asgeir Snow-Shod - Living son who helps run the family business * Unmid Snow-Shod - Son who serves as a guard captain * Lilija Snow-Shod - Deceased daughter whose loss deeply affects her * Maven Black-Briar - Maintains cautious relationship as prominent Riften citizen', 'Serves as Riften''s primary priestess of Talos, maintaining his shrine and providing spiritual guidance to worshippers. She also acts as a healer, though this role has diminished since her daughter''s death.', '* Proficient in Restoration magic and healing practices * Knowledge of religious rites and ceremonies * Skilled herbalist and alchemist * Capable of basic combat magic including Frostbite spell * Defensive magic expertise with Lesser Ward', 'Speaks with formal religious diction, frequently invoking Talos'' name and offering blessings. Her tone carries both maternal warmth and underlying sadness, especially when discussing faith or family.', '* Preserve Talos worship in Riften despite Imperial persecution * Honor her daughter''s memory by maintaining religious traditions * Support Skyrim''s independence to ensure religious freedom * Train new healers and priests to continue Talos'' worship');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nurelion', 'Nurelion is a brilliant but ailing High Elf alchemist who runs The White Phial shop in Windhelm, dedicating his life''s work to finding the legendary artifact of the same name. His deteriorating health and obsession with the White Phial drive him to increasingly desperate measures as he races against time to fulfill his life''s ambition.', 'highelf, alchemist, scholar, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Originally from the Summerset Isles, Nurelion established himself in Windhelm after decades of research into ancient Nordic alchemy. His discovery of historical records mentioning the White Phial led him to settle in Skyrim''s ancient capital, where he opened his shop and spent years tracking down the artifact''s location. His reputation as a master alchemist drew many apprentices, though few could tolerate his demanding nature.', 'Nurelion is short-tempered, impatient, and often condescending, particularly towards those he deems intellectually inferior. Despite his harsh exterior, he harbors a genuine passion for alchemy and a deep-seated desire to make a lasting contribution to his field. His illness has made him increasingly bitter and desperate, though his dedication to his work remains undiminished.', 'A tall, elderly High Elf with the characteristic golden skin of his race, though now pale and sickly from his illness. His face shows deep wrinkles and his posture, once proud and straight, has begun to stoop with age and infirmity. His hands, despite their slight tremor, still maintain the precision necessary for alchemy.', '* Quintus Navale - His apprentice and assistant, whom he treats harshly despite the young man''s dedication * Local Nords - Generally distant relationships due to both racial prejudice and his own antisocial nature * Windhelm''s Court Wizard - Occasional professional contact for magical supplies and scholarly discourse * Various Merchants - Business connections maintained purely for access to rare alchemical ingredients', 'Nurelion owns and operates The White Phial, one of Windhelm''s premier alchemy shops. Beyond selling potions and ingredients, he conducts extensive research into ancient Nordic alchemy, particularly focusing on legendary artifacts. His reputation draws customers from across Skyrim seeking his expertise in rare and powerful potions.', '* Master-level knowledge of alchemy and potion-making * Expert understanding of rare and magical ingredients * Scholarly expertise in ancient Nordic artifacts and their properties * Basic proficiency in magic, particularly in schools relating to alchemy * Extensive knowledge of rare alchemical recipes and techniques', 'Speaks in a sharp, dismissive tone with frequent sighs of exasperation and scholarly terminology. His speech often includes cutting remarks and impatient interruptions, though his voice has weakened with his illness.', '* Locate and retrieve the legendary White Phial before his illness claims him * Document his alchemical discoveries for future generations * Prove the superiority of his alchemical theories to the scholarly community * Ensure his life''s work continues through his reluctantly chosen successor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('octieve_san', 'Octieve San is a world-weary Breton elder living in Solitude, struggling with gambling debts and a drinking habit that has come to define his twilight years. Despite his gruff exterior and cynical outlook, he maintains a complex relationship with his daughter Evette while dealing with the consequences of his vices.', 'breton, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally a capable warrior in his younger days, Octieve settled in Solitude to raise his daughter Evette after likely losing his wife (circumstances unknown). His transition from warrior to civilian life proved challenging, leading him to seek solace in drinking and gambling at the Winking Skeever, gradually accumulating significant debts to Irnskar Ironhand.', 'Octieve is a cynical and grumpy individual who uses alcohol to cope with the frustrations of aging and his diminished status in society. Though often dismissive and short-tempered, he shows moments of warmth when treated with kindness, suggesting his bitter exterior masks deeper regrets and emotional pain. His relationship with his daughter reveals both his dependency and his shame at not being a better provider.', 'An elderly Breton man with the weathered features and stooped posture typical of advanced age. His face likely bears the ruddy complexion common to habitual drinkers, with deep wrinkles and aged skin telling the story of a hard-lived life.', '* Evette San - His daughter and caretaker, their relationship is strained by his behavior but bound by family duty * Irnskar Ironhand - Creditor and source of ongoing stress due to gambling debts * Corpulus Vinius - Owner of the Winking Skeever, who tolerates his regular presence * Various Solitude guards - Maintain a watchful eye on his public drinking', 'Retired warrior who now spends his days as a regular fixture at the Winking Skeever. His daughter''s success in running her spiced wine business allows him to live without working, though this appears to be a source of both relief and shame for him.', '* Former proficiency in Two-handed weapons, now mainly used to instruct others * Experienced gambler, though not particularly successful * Knowledge of warrior techniques from his younger days * Basic survival skills from his previous life as a warrior', 'Speaks in a gruff, world-weary tone with frequent complaints about his age and life''s hardships. His speech often carries undertones of self-pity and cynicism, frequently punctuated by references to drinking.', '* Clear his gambling debts to Irnskar Ironhand * Maintain his dignity despite his reduced circumstances * Improve his relationship with his daughter Evette * Find someone to share his remaining years with, as evidenced by his marriage availability');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('odahviing', 'Odahviing is an ancient and powerful dragon who becomes an unlikely ally to the Last Dragonborn after being captured in an elaborate trap at Dragonsreach. Initially serving Alduin, he later questions his master''s supremacy and aids the Dragonborn in their quest to defeat the World-Eater, becoming one of their most formidable allies.', 'dragon', '', '', 'sk_odahviing', '', 'Originally one of Alduin''s trusted lieutenants during the Dragon War and following his return. After witnessing the Dragonborn''s growing power and questioning Alduin''s true strength, he allowed himself to be lured into a trap at Dragonsreach, partly to test the Dragonborn''s Thu''um himself. This encounter led to his eventual alliance with the Dragonborn following Alduin''s defeat.', 'Proud and calculating, with a pragmatic approach to loyalty that''s typical of dovah nature. Though initially arrogant and deceptive, he shows respect for strength and cunning, eventually becoming genuinely loyal to the Dragonborn after recognizing their superior Thu''um. Maintains a formal, aristocratic demeanor befitting his status as an ancient dragon.', 'A massive red-scaled dragon with distinctive horns and wing structure. His physical form embodies the fearsome might of the dov, with powerful jaws capable of breathing fire and wings strong enough to carry multiple passengers.', '* Alduin - Former master whose authority he came to question * The Last Dragonborn - Current ally and leader he chose to follow after proving their strength * Paarthurnax - Fellow dragon who also broke from Alduin''s leadership * Other Dragons - Complex relationships ranging from former allies to potential rivals', 'Serves as a powerful ally and transportation for the Dragonborn, available when called upon through his namesake shout. Originally one of Alduin''s lieutenants before switching allegiance.', '* Master of the Thu''um, particularly proficient with fire-based shouts * Exceptional aerial combat capabilities * Formidable physical strength and durability typical of ancient dragons * Strategic military knowledge from centuries of experience * Extensive knowledge of dragon culture and history', 'Speaks in a formal, grandiose manner, frequently incorporating Dovahzul (dragon language) into his speech. His voice carries the weight of ancient wisdom and power, often using archaic phrasings and philosophical observations.', '* Serve the Dragonborn as a trusted ally and prove the wisdom of his choice to switch allegiance * Maintain his position of respect among other dragons who might question his choices * Help establish a new order among the dov under the Dragonborn''s leadership');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('odar', 'Odar is a perceptive and skilled Nord cook who serves at the Blue Palace in Solitude, using his unassuming position to gather intelligence about court politics and social dynamics. Though seemingly just a humble chef, he possesses keen observational skills and an intimate knowledge of the palace''s inner workings, making him an unwitting repository of valuable political insights.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Odar learned the culinary arts from an early age, likely apprenticing under a previous palace cook. Through years of dedicated service and exceptional skill, he earned his position at the Blue Palace, where he has witnessed the rise and fall of multiple Jarls, including the transition from High King Torygg to Jarl Elisif the Fair.', 'Odar is observant and quietly intelligent, maintaining a humble demeanor that allows him to blend into the background while gathering information. He takes immense pride in his culinary craft, viewing cooking as an art form equal to bardic performances, while maintaining a practical and straightforward approach to both his work and social interactions.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the typical robust build of his race, weathered by years of kitchen work. His hands show the calluses and minor burns of his profession, while his face likely bears the ruddy complexion common to those who spend their days near hot ovens and cooking fires.', '* Sybille Stentor - Wary of the court wizard, noting her unusual eating habits * Jarl Elisif - Professionally respectful but privately skeptical of her leadership * General Tullius - Recognizes him as the true power in Solitude * Jorn - Friendly relationship with the bard who appreciates his cooking * Palace Staff - Maintains cordial working relationships with fellow servants', 'As the head cook at the Blue Palace, Odar is responsible for preparing meals for the Jarl, her court, and the palace staff. His position requires him to manage the kitchen, plan menus, and ensure the quality of all food served within the palace, while maintaining the high standards expected of a royal kitchen.', '* Master-level cooking ability with expertise in Nordic cuisine * Excellent organizational and kitchen management capabilities * Keen observation skills and ability to gather information discreetly * Basic knowledge of local herbs and ingredients * Competent with a kitchen knife, carrying an iron dagger for practical use', 'Odar speaks in a direct, unembellished manner typical of working-class Nords, often sharing his observations matter-of-factly without concern for political correctness. His tone carries the confidence of someone secure in their profession but remains respectful of social hierarchies.', '* Maintain his position as the Blue Palace''s master cook * Perfect his culinary craft and expand his repertoire of recipes * Continue gathering interesting gossip and observations about court life * Possibly compile his knowledge and recipes into a cookbook for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('odfel', 'Odfel is a hardworking Nord miner in Shor''s Stone who takes immense pride in his mining abilities and former military service. Despite his gruff exterior and confrontational nature, he harbors romantic feelings for the local merchant Grelka and struggles with maintaining domestic harmony in his shared living space.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally serving as a soldier in Skyrim''s military forces, Odfel eventually traded his weapon for a pickaxe and settled in the mining village of Shor''s Stone. His transition from warrior to miner was driven by a desire for a more stable life, though he frequently boasts that mining presents greater challenges than his previous military career.', 'Odfel is brash, self-assured, and often confrontational, taking pride in his work ethic while looking down on those he deems lazy or unworthy. Despite his tough exterior, he shows a softer side in his unrequited feelings for Grelka and demonstrates a particular fixation on cleanliness and order, especially in his domestic life.', 'A sturdy Nord with the muscular build typical of someone who spends their days working in the mines. His body bears the calluses and weathering of hard physical labor, with strong arms and shoulders developed from years of wielding both weapons and mining tools.', '* Grogmar gro-Burzag - Contentious housemate with whom he frequently argues about cleanliness * Grelka - Local merchant whom he pursues romantically, though she rejects his advances * Filnjar - Town authority figure who mediates disputes between Odfel and Grogmar * Fellow miners - Professional relationships maintained through shared work experience', 'Odfel works as a full-time miner in Redbelly Mine, spending twelve hours daily extracting iron ore. His dedication to his work is evident in his long shifts and careful maintenance of his mining equipment, including his prized pickaxe which he''s named Rocksplinter.', '* Expert mining abilities with particular expertise in iron ore extraction * Former military combat training and experience * Physical strength and endurance developed through years of mining * Basic weapon handling and defensive capabilities from his soldier days * Domestic organization and cleaning expertise', 'Odfel speaks in a direct, often boastful manner, frequently comparing his current mining work to his past military service. His speech is peppered with complaints about his living situation and references to his mining prowess, delivered in a gruff Nord accent.', '* Earn enough money to secure his own private residence away from Grogmar * Win the affections of Grelka through persistent courtship * Maintain his reputation as one of Shor''s Stone''s most capable miners * Keep Redbelly Mine operating at peak efficiency * Prove his superior mining abilities through various workplace challenges');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('odvan', 'Odvan is a wrongfully imprisoned Breton in Cidhna Mine who maintains his innocence while adapting to prison life by joining the Forsworn movement. Despite his claims of being framed for murder by the Nords, he has learned to navigate the harsh realities of imprisonment while holding onto hope through thoughts of his family outside.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally a free citizen of Markarth, Odvan lived a relatively normal life until he was arrested for a murder he claims he didn''t commit while sleeping off mead at his aunt''s house. His imprisonment in Cidhna Mine led him to join the Forsworn movement for survival and protection, though he wasn''t affiliated with them prior to his incarceration.', 'Talkative and somewhat naive, Odvan maintains an optimistic outlook despite his circumstances, often speaking about his innocence and family. He shows adaptability in joining the Forsworn for survival, yet retains a rebellious streak evidenced by his discussions about potentially attacking guards. His casual demeanor and openness about his situation suggest he hasn''t been hardened by prison life to the degree of other inmates.', 'A typical Breton male with the characteristic smaller stature and lighter build common to his race. Years of mining have likely given him a somewhat muscular physique despite the harsh conditions and limited nutrition of prison life.', '* Bothela - His grandmother/aunt (relationship unclear) who runs The Hag''s Cure in Markarth * Duach - Fellow prisoner with whom he discusses escape plans * Forsworn Prisoners - Adopted brothers-in-arms within Cidhna Mine * Markarth Guards - Antagonistic relationship due to his alleged false imprisonment', 'Prisoner and silver miner in Cidhna Mine, forced to work in the infamous prison mine of Markarth. Prior to his imprisonment, his occupation is unknown, though his connection to Bothela suggests possible involvement in alchemy or traditional Reach practices.', '* Proficient in basic magic including Oakflesh, Raise Zombie, and Flames spells * Experienced in mining and basic survival skills developed in Cidhna Mine * Capable of wielding improvised weapons like shivs * Basic knowledge of alchemy possibly learned from his grandmother Bothela', 'Uses casual, informal speech patterns with frequent contractions and a conversational tone. His manner of speaking reflects his relative youth and common background, without the hardened edge typical of long-term prisoners.', '* Prove his innocence and secure release from Cidhna Mine * Reunite with his grandmother/aunt Bothela * Survive prison life through alliance with the Forsworn * Eventually escape imprisonment through any means necessary');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('oengul_war-anvil', 'Oengul War-Anvil is Windhelm''s master blacksmith and the primary weaponsmith for the Stormcloak rebellion, driven by his fierce determination to prove himself superior to Eorlund Gray-Mane of Whiterun. A dedicated craftsman and loyal supporter of Ulfric Stormcloak, he works tirelessly at his forge to arm the rebellion while training the next generation of Nordic smiths.', 'nord, blacksmith, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Oengul learned the art of smithing from a young age, developing his skills through years of dedicated practice in the harsh climate of Skyrim''s northern reaches. His unwavering support for the traditional Nordic way of life and deep respect for ancient smithing techniques led him to align with Ulfric Stormcloak''s cause, eventually earning him the position of chief blacksmith for the rebellion.', 'Prideful and competitive, Oengul is consumed by his rivalry with Eorlund Gray-Mane and his desire to prove himself the finest smith in Skyrim. Though gruff and sometimes short-tempered, he shows a softer side in his patient mentoring of Hermir Strong-Heart, revealing a deep commitment to passing on Nordic smithing traditions. His fierce loyalty to the Stormcloak cause and traditional Nordic values shapes every aspect of his work and interactions.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of a lifelong blacksmith. His face bears the weathered features common to those who work long hours at the forge, with callused hands and burn scars telling the tale of his dedication to his craft. His aging but still-robust physique reflects decades of hammering at the anvil.', '* Hermir Strong-Heart - Apprentice blacksmith whom he mentors with stern but genuine care * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respected leader whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Eorlund Gray-Mane - Professional rival whom he''s determined to surpass * Stormcloak Soldiers - Valued customers and comrades in the rebellion * Imperial Legion - Viewed as enemies of true Nordic traditions', 'As Windhelm''s master blacksmith, Oengul creates and maintains weapons and armor for both the Stormcloak army and private citizens. He manages the city''s primary forge and smithy, overseeing all aspects of metalwork while training his apprentice in traditional Nordic smithing techniques.', '* Master-level blacksmithing with expertise in traditional Nordic weapon and armor crafting * Specialized knowledge of military-grade equipment manufacturing * Skilled warrior capable of wielding heavy weapons, particularly warhammers * Expert in metal refinement and material selection for weaponry * Proficient teacher of smithing techniques', 'Speaks in a gruff, direct manner with a thick Nordic accent, often incorporating references to smithing and traditional Nordic values. His speech is colored by competitive remarks about his rival Eorlund Gray-Mane and passionate declarations of support for the Stormcloak cause.', '* Surpass Eorlund Gray-Mane''s reputation to become recognized as Skyrim''s finest smith * Ensure the success of the Stormcloak rebellion through superior arms and armor * Pass on traditional Nordic smithing techniques to the next generation through his apprentice * Maintain Windhelm''s position as a center of Nordic craftsmanship');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('oglub', 'Oglub is an elderly Orc miner who has dedicated his twilight years to serving Dushnikh Yal stronghold through steadfast labor in its orichalcum mines. Despite his warrior heritage and relation to Ghorbash the Iron Hand, he has accepted a humble role that befits his advanced age, embodying the Orcish values of duty and respect for hierarchy.', 'orc, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Dushnikh Yal, Oglub grew up training as a warrior alongside his brother Ghorbash, but never achieved the position of chief. As age caught up with him, he transitioned from warrior to miner, accepting his place in the stronghold''s hierarchy with dignity rather than challenging for leadership as younger Orcs might.', 'Oglub is humble, resigned, and deeply respectful of tradition and authority, having made peace with his position in life. He maintains a quiet dignity in his work, showing neither resentment nor ambition, though he occasionally reveals a hint of pride in his brother Ghorbash''s continuing spirit.', 'Oglub is an elderly Orc with weathered green skin and prominent tusks that show signs of wear. His muscular frame, though still impressive by human standards, has begun to show the effects of age and years of physical labor in the mines. His hands are calloused and scarred from decades of work with pickaxe and ore.', '* Ghorbash the Iron Hand - Younger brother, whom he respects but won''t encourage to challenge authority * Chief Burguk - His chief, whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Ghak, Mahk, and Dulug - Fellow miners with whom he shares daily labor * Dushnikh Yal Community - Respected elder worker within the stronghold', 'Oglub serves as one of the primary miners in Dushnikh Mine, extracting valuable orichalcum ore crucial to the stronghold''s economy and crafting needs. His tireless work ethic sees him spending all his time in the mines, maintaining a constant schedule of mining, eating, and brief periods of rest.', '* Experienced miner with deep knowledge of orichalcum extraction techniques * Retains basic warrior training from his younger days * Possesses considerable physical endurance despite his age * Knowledgeable about Orcish customs and traditions', 'Oglub speaks in a soft, tired voice that reflects his age and resignation to his role. His speech is direct and humble, often referring to his duty to the stronghold and his acceptance of his position.', '* Continue serving the stronghold through diligent mining work until his final days * Maintain the peace and prosperity of Dushnikh Yal through his labor * Support his brother Ghorbash while ensuring stability under Chief Burguk''s leadership');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ogmund', 'Ogmund is a renowned Nord skald (bard) and master of the ancient Nordic oral traditions residing in Markarth. As one of Skyrim''s most influential bards, his songs and techniques continue to be taught at the Bards College, while his unwavering devotion to Talos and the Stormcloak cause marks him as both a cultural preservationist and political dissenter.', 'nord, bard, reach', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Ogmund spent his youth traveling across the province as a wandering bard, collecting stories and songs from every hold. He studied at the Bards College in Solitude, where he later became influential enough that his techniques and compositions became part of the standard curriculum. His experiences in war and battle have shaped many of his most famous ballads, though the specific conflicts he participated in remain unclear.', 'Ogmund is proud, sometimes abrasive, and firmly set in his traditional Nord values. He carries himself with the confidence of a master of his craft, often dismissive of lesser-skilled performers, yet willing to share his knowledge with those who show genuine interest and respect for the old ways. His devotion to Talos and the Stormcloak cause reveals a deeply patriotic and politically conscious character beneath his artistic persona.', 'An elderly Nord male with the weathered features of one who has spent many years traveling Skyrim''s harsh lands. His strong, commanding presence and straight posture defy his advanced age, while his voice remains powerful and clear from years of performing. His hands show the calluses of both a warrior and a musician.', '* Kleppr - Professional relationship with the innkeeper of Silver-Blood Inn * Bards College - Respected elder whose works are still taught to students * Ondolemar - Antagonistic relationship due to Ogmund''s Talos worship * Local Markarth residents - Generally well-respected figure among the common folk', 'Ogmund serves as the resident bard at the Silver-Blood Inn, where he performs traditional Nordic ballads and epic poems. As an expert trainer in Speech, he also takes on students seeking to improve their persuasive abilities and bardic skills.', '* Master of Nordic oral traditions and bardic performance * Expert level Speech capabilities and training abilities * Competent warrior skilled with sword and shield * Extensive knowledge of Nordic history and folklore * Accomplished composer and songwriter', 'Ogmund speaks in a gruff, direct manner with the authoritative tone of someone who knows their own worth. His speech is peppered with references to battles and old Nordic traditions, often delivered with a hint of condescension toward those he deems less knowledgeable.', '* Preserve and pass on traditional Nordic songs and stories to future generations * Maintain his worship of Talos despite Imperial and Thalmor persecution * Support the Stormcloak cause through his influential position as a respected bard * Continue performing and teaching until his dying day');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ogol', 'Ogol is a unique Orc warrior who stands out among his stronghold kin for his adoption of city-dwelling customs and attire, while still maintaining deep loyalty to tribal traditions. Despite being elder to the current chief Gularzob, he demonstrates humility and dedication to serving his tribe''s interests, embodying the complex balance between progress and tradition within Orc society.', 'orc, warrior, rift, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Largashbur, Ogol spent significant time traveling between Orc strongholds and Skyrim''s cities, gaining exposure to different cultures and ways of life. His experiences outside traditional Orc society influenced his choice to adopt city-style clothing and customs, though he never abandoned his core tribal values. During the period of Malacath''s curse on Largashbur, he remained steadfast in defending his home despite the hardships faced by his people.', 'Ogol exhibits a pragmatic and measured approach to life, balancing traditional Orcish values with more progressive attitudes learned from his time among city-dwellers. He shows remarkable humility and loyalty in accepting leadership from a younger chief, demonstrating the Orcish virtue of putting tribal harmony above personal pride. While initially suspicious of outsiders, he becomes respectful and loyal to those who prove their worth to the tribe.', 'Ogol is a sturdy, well-built Orc with the characteristic green skin and tusks of his race, though his tusks are slightly smaller than average. His face bears the typical battle scars of an Orc warrior, and his posture reflects years of combat training and discipline. His muscular frame is lean rather than bulky, suggesting agility as well as strength.', '* Chief Gularzob - Younger tribal leader whom Ogol serves loyally despite being his elder * Largashbur Tribe Members - Family bonds through shared tribal membership * Malacath - Devoted follower of the Orcish deity * The Dragonborn - Respected ally after lifting Malacath''s curse', 'Ogol serves as a warrior and defender of Largashbur, combining traditional Orcish combat duties with diplomatic interactions with outsiders due to his familiarity with non-Orc customs. His role includes both protecting the stronghold and maintaining its connections with the outside world.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat, particularly with war axes * Capable archer with training in hunting and warfare * Experienced in light armor combat techniques * Knowledge of both tribal Orcish traditions and city customs * Basic hunting and survival skills', 'Ogol speaks in direct, practical terms with a slight formal edge that reflects his exposure to city life. His speech patterns blend traditional Orcish directness with more sophisticated vocabulary picked up from his time among non-Orcs.', '* Maintain the strength and unity of Largashbur under its new leadership * Bridge the gap between traditional Orcish ways and modern Skyrim society * Serve and protect his tribe while adapting to changing times * Uphold the teachings of Malacath while embracing beneficial outside influences');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('king_olaf_one-eye', 'King Olaf One-Eye was a controversial High King of Skyrim during the First Era who became infamous for his alleged deception and betrayal of his people. Now risen as a powerful draugr, he continues to defend his legacy and secrets within Dead Men''s Respite, serving as a fearsome guardian of ancient Nordic knowledge and power.', 'nord', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Originally the Jarl of Whiterun, Olaf rose to become High King of Skyrim after allegedly defeating the dragon Numinex in single combat, though some sources dispute this claim. Historical accounts written by the bard Svaknir suggest that Olaf actually used treachery to trap Numinex and fabricated the tale of his heroic victory to gain the throne. After his death, his body was interred in Dead Men''s Respite, where dark magic transformed him into a powerful draugr.', 'Even in undeath, Olaf maintains the commanding presence and arrogance of a king, viewing all who enter his tomb as subjects to be dominated or intruders to be destroyed. His personality is marked by pride, territoriality, and an unyielding desire to maintain his version of historical events. Despite his corrupted state, he retains the tactical intelligence and leadership qualities that once made him a successful ruler.', 'A towering Nord draugr with distinctive ancient Nordic bone structure and imposing physicality, even in his undead state. His most notable feature is his missing left eye, which now glows with an otherworldly energy. His desiccated flesh and preserved musculature suggest he was a powerful warrior in life.', '* Svaknir - Bitter enemy who exposed his deceptions through poetry * Numinex - The dragon he allegedly defeated, though the truth remains disputed * Citizens of Whiterun - Former subjects during his time as Jarl * Other Draugr - Commands them within Dead Men''s Respite as their king * Bards College - Antagonistic relationship due to their preservation of Svaknir''s unflattering verses', 'As a draugr, Olaf serves as the guardian of Dead Men''s Respite, protecting ancient Nordic secrets and his own remains. In life, he served as both Jarl of Whiterun and High King of Skyrim, ruling during a crucial period in the region''s history.', '* Master of Nordic combat techniques, particularly proficient with two-handed weapons * Capable of channeling powerful magical energy through his empty eye socket * Natural leader with tactical military expertise * Possesses the enhanced strength and supernatural abilities common to powerful draugr * Retains knowledge of ancient Thu''um (Dragon Shouts)', 'Speaks in archaic Nordic dialect with a commanding, resonant voice that echoes with supernatural power. His speech patterns reflect his royal background, using formal language and authoritative tones even in undeath.', '* Protect his tomb and the secrets contained within Dead Men''s Respite * Maintain his version of historical events by preventing the truth from being discovered * Eliminate any who would threaten his legacy or expose his possible deceptions * Continue his reign as king, even in death, by maintaining dominion over his burial chamber');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('olaf_one-eye', 'Olaf One-Eye was a legendary Nord warrior who rose from Jarl of Whiterun to High King of Skyrim during the First Era, most famous for his supposed defeat and capture of the dragon Numinex. His controversial reign was marked by both great achievements in unifying Skyrim and accusations of deception, leading to a complex legacy that endures into the Fourth Era.', 'nord', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born in the First Era, Olaf began his career as a warrior and leader in Whiterun, eventually becoming its Jarl through his martial prowess and leadership abilities. His claimed victory over the dragon Numinex atop Mount Anthor, using both the Thu''um and conventional warfare, catapulted him to fame and eventually led to his elevation as High King of Skyrim in 1E 420, where he ruled for 32 years. After death, he earned his place in Sovngarde among the greatest Nordic heroes.', 'Olaf is proud and authoritative, carrying himself with the bearing of both warrior and king. While stern and uncompromising in matters of honor and duty, he shows a capacity for reconciliation and respect even toward former enemies, as demonstrated by his eventual acceptance of Svaknir. He values strength and courage above all, but also possesses the diplomatic acumen expected of a High King.', 'A tall, muscular Nord warrior bearing the battle-scars of countless conflicts, most notably missing one eye. His remaining eye reflects the fierce determination and commanding presence that helped him rise to power. His bearing and posture, even in death, conveys the dignity and strength of a Nordic king.', '* Numinex - His greatest adversary, whose defeat became the cornerstone of his legend * Svaknir - Initially his critic and enemy, later earned his respect as an honest opponent * People of Whiterun - His original subjects who helped construct Dragonsreach in his honor * Other Jarls of Skyrim - Initially peers, later became his subordinates as High King * Citizens of Solitude - Maintain a complex relationship through their burning of his effigy in annual festival', 'Olaf served first as Jarl of Whiterun, where he ordered the construction of Dragonsreach to house his captured dragon. He later became High King of Skyrim, ruling for 32 years and achieving significant territorial expansions including the conquest of The Reach. In death, he resides as an honored soul in Sovngarde.', '* Master of the Thu''um, capable of engaging in battle with dragons * Exceptional warrior and military commander * Skilled diplomat and political leader * Expert in Nordic combat traditions and warfare * Accomplished dragon hunter and strategist', 'Olaf speaks with the formal, commanding tone of ancient Nordic nobility, favoring archaic expressions and warrior''s terminology. His speech carries the weight of authority, often incorporating references to honor, battle, and Nordic traditions.', '* Maintain his honor and legacy in Sovngarde * Aid the Last Dragonborn in defeating Alduin * Reconcile with former enemies like Svaknir in the afterlife * Protect the glory and traditions of Nordic culture even in death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('olava_the_feeble', 'Olava the Feeble is a mysterious elderly Nord seer living in Whiterun who possesses genuine prophetic abilities and maintains secretive connections to the Dark Brotherhood. Despite her frail appearance and self-deprecating moniker, she wields considerable spiritual power and knowledge of future events, serving as a cryptic guide to those deemed worthy of her insights.', 'nord, witch, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born with the gift of prophecy, Olava spent her early years struggling to understand and control her visions, eventually learning to harness them through decades of practice and meditation. Her connection to the Dark Brotherhood was forged in her younger years, though the exact nature of this relationship remains shrouded in mystery, suggesting she may have once served as their mystic advisor. She chose to settle in Whiterun in her later years, seeking a quiet life while still maintaining her role as a seer for those who truly need her guidance.', 'Olava is deliberately cryptic and selective about sharing her gift, often testing those who seek her wisdom to determine their worthiness. Despite her advanced age and apparent physical weakness, she maintains a sharp mind and strong will, using her mysterious demeanor to both protect herself and maintain control over her interactions. She carries the weight of her dark visions with stoic acceptance, having long ago made peace with her role as a bearer of both fortunate and unfortunate futures.', 'A weathered elderly Nord woman with deep wrinkles etched into her face and pale, almost translucent skin that speaks to her advanced age. Her frame is slight and frail-looking, earning her the moniker ''the Feeble'', though her eyes remain sharp and penetrating, often described as having an unsettling, knowing quality that seems to peer through people rather than at them.', '* Dark Brotherhood - Mysterious connection as a seer and possible former advisor * Whiterun Guards - Maintain a respectful distance, viewing her with a mixture of fear and reverence * Local Citizens - Generally avoided by most due to her reputation and cryptic nature * Select Clients - Forms brief but significant connections with those she chooses to read for', 'Olava serves as Whiterun''s resident seer, providing prophetic readings to those she deems worthy while maintaining a modest lifestyle from the payments she receives. Her true occupation extends beyond simple fortune-telling, as she appears to serve as a mystical gateway between the present and future, particularly in matters concerning the Dark Brotherhood.', '* Powerful prophetic abilities allowing her to see detailed visions of the future * Deep understanding of mystical arts and divination * Keen insight into human nature and motivations * Ability to interpret and communicate complex visions in meaningful ways', 'She speaks in cryptic riddles and metaphors, often mixing straightforward statements with mysterious prophecies and dark omens. Her voice carries an otherworldly quality that commands attention despite its aged tremor, and she frequently employs dramatic pauses for emphasis.', '* Preserve and properly utilize her gift of prophecy by sharing visions only with those truly deserving * Maintain her connection to the Dark Brotherhood while keeping her exact role secret * Guide those whose futures she sees as significant toward their destined paths * Find a worthy successor to pass on her knowledge of the prophetic arts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('old_orc', 'A world-weary Orc warrior who has reached the twilight of his years and seeks an honorable death in combat as promised by Malacath. Having already proven his might by slaying two sabre cats, he waits patiently for a worthy opponent to grant him the glorious end he believes he deserves.', 'orc, warrior', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in an Orc stronghold, he lived by the strict traditional codes of Malacath''s followers. Though he fought valiantly throughout his life and earned respect among his kin, he never achieved the position of chief, and now age prevents him from following the traditional path of taking wives and leading a clan. His recent vision from Malacath has led him to seek out his final battle.', 'Stoic, traditional, and uncompromising in his beliefs about the proper way for an Orc to live and die. He displays a quiet dignity and philosophical acceptance of his fate, showing neither fear nor hesitation in the face of death. His adherence to Orcish customs and religious beliefs shapes every aspect of his worldview.', 'A weathered and battle-scarred Orc male of advanced years, though still maintaining an impressive muscular build typical of his race. His tusks show signs of wear, and his face bears the marks of countless battles, yet his posture remains proud and warrior-like, betraying no weakness despite his age.', '* Malacath - Primary deity and spiritual guide whose promise of a good death he faithfully awaits * Former Stronghold Members - Distant relations he has left behind to seek his destiny * Sabre Cats - Recent opponents he defeated, proving he still maintains his warrior prowess', 'Wandering warrior seeking his final battle. Though technically classified as a bandit in game terms, he is more accurately described as a traditional Orcish warrior following his cultural customs to their conclusion.', '* Exceptional heavy armor combat training typical of Orcish warriors * Skilled with traditional Orcish weapons, particularly war axes and heavy weapons * Proven capability in beast combat, as evidenced by his defeat of two sabre cats * Survival skills necessary for living in the wilderness', 'Speaks in a direct, gruff manner typical of Orcs, but with an underlying tone of wisdom and acceptance. His words are carefully chosen and philosophical, focusing on matters of honor, tradition, and proper death.', '* Find a worthy opponent to grant him the good death promised by Malacath * Die with honor while still maintaining his strength and dignity * Uphold traditional Orcish values even in his final moments');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('olda', 'Olda is a hardworking Nord lumberjack living in Dragon Bridge who finds herself trapped in an increasingly frustrating marriage with her alcoholic husband Horgeir. Despite her gruff exterior, she is a practical and determined woman who has taken on much of the responsibility for maintaining their household while harboring growing feelings for her brother-in-law Lodvar.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh climate of Skyrim, Olda learned the value of hard work from an early age. She married Horgeir when the Dragon Bridge lumber mill was still prosperous, but has watched their fortunes decline due to her husband''s growing dependence on alcohol. What started as a promising partnership has devolved into a strained relationship marked by financial troubles and broken promises.', 'Olda is direct and no-nonsense, with little patience for pleasantries or excuses. She faces problems head-on and isn''t afraid to speak her mind, particularly regarding her husband''s destructive behavior. Though outwardly harsh, her actions reveal a practical woman who works diligently to maintain order in her life despite challenging circumstances.', 'Olda is a sturdy Nord woman with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. Her face shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors regularly, with calloused hands and strong arms from years of handling lumber. Her features carry the characteristic Nordic structure with a prominent brow and strong jaw.', '* Horgeir - Her husband, whose drinking problem has strained their marriage to the breaking point * Lodvar - Brother-in-law whom she has developed romantic feelings for, though likely unexpressed * Dragon Bridge Guards - Views them with suspicion and concern over their growing presence * Local Townspeople - Maintains minimal but practical relationships with neighbors', 'As a lumberjack at the Dragon Bridge lumber mill, Olda handles various aspects of the lumber business while her husband''s reliability diminishes. She maintains their home through daily chores and upkeep, effectively managing both domestic and professional responsibilities.', '* Experienced lumberjack capable of handling heavy equipment and processing timber * Proficient in household management and maintenance * Skilled at identifying and storing various types of wood * Basic weapon proficiency with an iron dagger for self-defense', 'Olda speaks in a blunt, straightforward manner with a strong Nordic accent, often using cutting remarks and showing little concern for social niceties. Her speech is practical and to-the-point, frequently tinged with frustration or sarcasm.', '* Resolve her husband''s drinking problem, either through intervention or more drastic measures * Secure the financial stability of the lumber mill before it''s lost to creditors * Find personal happiness, potentially through a relationship with Lodvar * Maintain independence and control over her domestic situation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('olfina_gray-mane', 'Olfina Gray-Mane is a proud Nord woman from one of Whiterun''s most prominent families, caught between tradition and forbidden love. She embodies the strength and independence of Nord women while secretly maintaining a romance with Jon Battle-Born, defying the bitter feud between their families.', 'nord, noble, whiterun, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born into the prestigious Gray-Mane clan of Whiterun, Olfina was raised amid the city''s political tensions and traditional Nord values. She grew up during a time when her family and the Battle-Borns were still friends, only to see their relationship deteriorate with the outbreak of the Civil War. Her upbringing in a warrior family and exposure to Skyforge Steel craftsmanship shaped her strong work ethic and pride in Nord heritage.', 'Fiercely independent and outspoken, Olfina challenges traditional gender roles while maintaining deep respect for Nord customs. She possesses a dual nature - publicly displaying a tough, confrontational exterior while privately harboring a romantic, rebellious spirit in her relationship with Jon Battle-Born. Despite her bold words and confident demeanor, she shows an interesting contradiction in her aversion to actual combat.', 'A strong-built Nord woman with the characteristic fair complexion of her race. She bears the proud bearing of the Gray-Mane family, with athletic physique developed from years of physical labor. Her features reflect her Nordic heritage, though she carries herself with more grace than the typical warrior.', '* Jon Battle-Born - Secret lover despite family feud * Vignar Gray-Mane - Uncle and Jarl (if Stormcloaks take Whiterun) * Eorlund Gray-Mane - Father, renowned blacksmith * Thorald Gray-Mane - Brother, missing in action * Battle-Born Clan - Rival family, though personally conflicted due to her relationship with Jon * Hulda - Employer at the Bannered Mare', 'Olfina serves as a barmaid at the Bannered Mare while also performing civic duties patrolling Whiterun. If the Stormcloaks capture Whiterun, she becomes housecarl to her uncle Vignar Gray-Mane, taking on the prestigious role of protecting the new Jarl.', '* Skilled in tavern management and customer service * Basic combat training with daggers * Political acumen from growing up in a prominent family * Stealth and discretion (demonstrated by maintaining a secret relationship) * Leadership capabilities (as shown by potential housecarl position)', 'Olfina speaks directly and assertively, often with a challenging tone that reflects her strong Nordic pride. She frequently makes bold statements about female strength and capability, though her actual combat behavior doesn''t always match her confident words.', '* Maintain her relationship with Jon Battle-Born despite family opposition * Prove herself as capable as any man in her chosen pursuits * Support her family''s interests while seeking peace between the feuding clans * Advance her position in Whiterun society * Find resolution regarding her missing brother Thorald');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('olfrid_battle-born', 'Olfrid Battle-Born is the proud patriarch of Whiterun''s wealthy Battle-Born clan and a fervent supporter of the Imperial cause. As a cunning political operator and businessman, he maintains his family''s dominance through a combination of legitimate enterprise and clandestine dealings with the Thieves Guild, while perpetuating a bitter feud with the rival Gray-Mane clan.', 'nord, noble, whiterun, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born into the prestigious Battle-Born clan, Olfrid inherited leadership of one of Whiterun''s oldest and most influential families. He built upon his ancestors'' legacy by expanding the clan''s wealth through shrewd business dealings and maintaining strong political ties to the Empire, while the Civil War has only deepened his family''s rivalry with the Stormcloak-supporting Gray-Manes.', 'Olfrid is an arrogant and confrontational man who takes immense pride in his family''s name and status. He''s quick to boast about the Battle-Borns'' wealth and achievements while showing open contempt for those he considers beneath him, particularly the Gray-Manes. Though outwardly honorable, he''s pragmatic enough to work with the Thieves Guild when it serves his interests.', 'A sturdy Nord male of advanced years with the bearing of a warrior turned nobleman. Despite his age, he maintains a strong physical presence that hints at his martial background, with weathered features and proud posture that command respect.', '* Idolaf Battle-Born - His son, whom he proudly supports in fighting for the Empire * Jon Battle-Born - His grandson, whose secret romance with Olfina Gray-Mane he would strongly disapprove of * Eorlund Gray-Mane - Former friend turned bitter rival due to Civil War allegiances * Maven Black-Briar - Business associate and fellow Thieves Guild contact * Clan Battle-Born - Patriarch and leader of the family * Imperial Legion - Staunch supporter and benefactor', 'Olfrid serves as the patriarch of Clan Battle-Born, managing the family''s extensive business interests and political connections in Whiterun. His position involves maintaining the clan''s wealth, status, and influence while representing their interests in city affairs.', '* Experienced warrior with traditional Nord combat training * Shrewd businessman and political operator * Expert in managing wealth and maintaining noble connections * Knowledgeable in Whiterun''s history and politics * Skilled negotiator and intimidator', 'Speaks with the authoritative tone of a nobleman, frequently reminding others of his clan''s importance and status. His speech is marked by boastful declarations and thinly-veiled contempt for his rivals, often using formal titles and clan names to emphasize social standing.', '* Maintain and expand the Battle-Born clan''s wealth and influence in Whiterun * Support the Imperial cause in the Civil War while undermining the Stormcloaks and their supporters * Ensure his family''s dominance over the rival Gray-Manes * Preserve the Battle-Born legacy for future generations * Strengthen ties with the Empire while protecting his secret dealings with the Thieves Guild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('olur', 'Olur is a diligent young Orc who serves as both apprentice smith and miner in the stronghold of Mor Khazgur, carrying the dual responsibilities of his position as the forgewife''s son. His tireless work ethic and dedication to traditional Orcish craftsmanship reflect his deep connection to his community, though he harbors a quiet curiosity about life beyond the stronghold walls.', 'orc, archer, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Mor Khazgur as the son of Chief Larak and his forgewife Shuftharz, Olur was groomed from an early age to follow in his mother''s footsteps as a skilled smith. His upbringing has been shaped by Orcish traditions and the expectations placed upon him as both the chief''s son and the forgewife''s apprentice. His father''s past service in the Legion has sparked an interest in the world beyond the stronghold, though duty keeps him bound to his people.', 'Olur is a reserved and dutiful individual who takes immense pride in his craftsmanship and responsibilities to the stronghold. His taciturn nature masks a thoughtful mind that contemplates both traditional Orcish ways and the possibilities of life beyond the stronghold walls. Though dedicated to his current roles, he shows signs of internal conflict between his obligations to his people and his curiosity about Legion service.', 'Olur possesses the typical robust build of an Orc male, with pronounced tusks and the characteristic green skin of his race. His muscular frame has been further developed by years of smithing and mining work, with particularly strong arms and shoulders from wielding hammers and pickaxes.', '* Chief Larak - Father and tribal leader, who shares stories of his Legion days * Shuftharz - Mother and forgewife, who trains him in smithing * Gul - Fellow miner and workmate during night shifts * Ghamorz - Mining colleague and occasional meal companion * Other stronghold members - Respectful but distant relationships', 'Olur serves dual roles in Mor Khazgur as both a smith''s apprentice and a miner. He maintains an exhausting schedule, working at the forge during daylight hours and mining through the night, demonstrating extraordinary stamina by apparently never sleeping.', '* Skilled blacksmith trained in traditional Orcish metalworking techniques * Proficient miner with experience in ore extraction * Capable warrior trained with both bow and war axe * Exceptional physical endurance, able to work extended hours without rest * Basic knowledge of Orcish armor and weapon crafting traditions', 'Olur speaks in brief, direct statements, focusing primarily on matters of work and duty. His manner of speech reflects both his reserved nature and the practical mindset of Orcish culture.', '* Master the art of Orcish smithing under his mother''s guidance * Maintain his position as a valuable contributor to the stronghold''s prosperity * Potentially explore opportunities to serve in the Imperial Legion, following his father''s footsteps * Uphold the honor and traditions of his people while considering his own path');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('omluag', 'Omluag is a downtrodden Breton laborer working at Markarth''s smelter under harsh conditions, secretly harboring sympathies for the Forsworn rebellion. Despite his oppressed status, he maintains a quiet resilience while dreaming of better working conditions and freedom from the Silver-Blood family''s exploitation.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born into poverty in Markarth, Omluag has spent his entire adult life working the dangerous smelters under increasingly oppressive conditions. His experiences with Nord discrimination and witnessing the Silver-Blood family''s cruel dominance over the Reach has led him to secretly support the Forsworn cause, though he''s never actively joined their rebellion.', 'Omluag is a beaten-down but quietly defiant worker who maintains his dignity despite harsh circumstances. He shows signs of depression and resignation about his situation, yet retains enough spirit to complain about working conditions when given the chance. Though fearful of authority, he harbors deep resentment toward his oppressors and sympathizes with resistance movements.', 'A middle-aged Breton male with the weathered appearance and callused hands typical of manual laborers. His body shows signs of burns and injuries from smelter work, and his posture reflects years of carrying heavy loads. His face bears the premature aging common to those working in extreme heat conditions.', '* Hathrasil - Roommate and fellow smelter worker who shares his living space in the Warrens * Mulush - Orc overseer who frequently abuses and mistreats him * Silver-Blood Family - Wealthy oppressors whom he secretly despises * Forsworn - Group he quietly sympathizes with, though maintains distance from * Other Warrens residents - Fellow downtrodden workers he shares community with', 'Omluag works as a smelter operator in Markarth''s Treasury House, performing dangerous and exhausting labor processing silver ore. His position represents the lowest rung of Markarth''s social ladder, working long hours under harsh conditions for minimal pay.', '* Experienced smelter worker with knowledge of metalworking processes * Basic self-defense abilities with an iron dagger * Physical endurance built up from years of manual labor * Survival skills necessary for living in Markarth''s poorest district', 'Speaks in short, cautious sentences, often looking over his shoulder for supervisors. His tone carries a mix of fear and bitter resignation, with occasional flashes of suppressed anger when discussing his working conditions.', '* Survive day-to-day life while maintaining some measure of dignity * Secure better working conditions and fair treatment at the smelter * See the Silver-Blood family''s power broken and workers freed from exploitation * Perhaps one day witness the Forsworn reclaim the Reach');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ondolemar', 'Ondolemar is a high-ranking Thalmor Justiciar stationed in Markarth, embodying the supreme confidence and racial superiority complex of the Aldmeri Dominion. As the chief enforcer of the Talos worship ban in the Reach, he represents the Dominion''s political and religious authority while carrying out his duties with characteristic Altmer sophistication and unwavering devotion to Thalmor ideology.', 'highelf, mage, reach, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born into the privileged upper echelons of Alinor society, Ondolemar was groomed from an early age for service in the Thalmor''s diplomatic corps. His exceptional magical aptitude and unwavering loyalty to Altmer supremacy ideology earned him the prestigious position of Justiciar, leading to his current assignment overseeing Thalmor interests in Markarth after the White-Gold Concordat.', 'Ondolemar is aristocratic, condescending, and absolutely convinced of mer superiority over men. While he maintains a veneer of diplomatic courtesy, he barely conceals his disdain for humans and what he considers their primitive beliefs. Despite his prejudices, he displays a dry wit and can be surprisingly pragmatic when it serves Thalmor interests.', 'Tall and slender like most Altmer, Ondolemar carries himself with perfect posture that emphasizes his height advantage over most races. His angular features are typical of his race, with high cheekbones and pointed ears, while his golden skin maintains its luster despite Markarth''s harsh climate. His eyes hold the characteristic amber glow of the Altmer, often narrowed in scrutiny of those around him.', '* Jarl Igmund - Political relationship marked by thinly-veiled tension and mutual necessity * Thalmor Soldiers - Two subordinate guards who accompany him constantly * Ogmund the Skald - Subject of investigation for suspected Talos worship * Thalmor Embassy - Regular correspondence with Ambassador Elenwen * Local Nords - Generally hostile relationship due to his role in suppressing Talos worship', 'As a Thalmor Justiciar, Ondolemar serves as the primary diplomatic and enforcement representative of the Aldmeri Dominion in Markarth. His primary duties include monitoring compliance with the White-Gold Concordat, particularly the ban on Talos worship, while maintaining political pressure on local authorities to ensure continued Thalmor influence.', '* Master-level proficiency in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Expert-level skill in Restoration and Alteration magic * Advanced diplomatic and interrogation techniques * Extensive knowledge of Imperial law and Thalmor protocols * Command and leadership expertise developed through years of military service', 'Speaks with cultured, precise diction and a subtle Alinor accent, favoring formal language that emphasizes his perceived superiority. His tone alternates between condescending politeness and barely-concealed contempt, particularly when addressing humans.', '* Advance Thalmor influence in Skyrim through careful political maneuvering * Completely eradicate Talos worship in the Reach * Maintain and strengthen the Dominion''s control over Imperial affairs * Secure personal advancement within the Thalmor hierarchy * Prove the superiority of mer over men through example and action');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('onmund', 'Onmund is a talented Nord mage who defied his family''s traditional anti-magic beliefs to pursue studies at the College of Winterhold. He represents a rare bridge between Nordic culture and magical scholarship, specializing in destruction magic while struggling to reconcile his heritage with his chosen path.', 'nord, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold, onmund', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born into a traditional Nord family that viewed magic with deep suspicion and disdain, Onmund spent years convincing his relatives that studying magic was his true calling. He eventually left his family behind, trading a cherished ancestral amulet for magical knowledge and enrolling at the College of Winterhold despite facing cultural stigma and familial disapproval.', 'Quiet and determined, Onmund displays both scholarly dedication and occasional self-doubt stemming from his cultural background. While proud of his Nordic heritage, he struggles with the conflict between traditional Nord values and his passion for magic, often feeling the need to prove himself worthy of both worlds. He shows particular enthusiasm for destruction magic, perhaps as a way to demonstrate that magical prowess can be as formidable as traditional Nordic warrior skills.', 'Onmund has the typical sturdy Nordic build with fair skin and light hair, though his frame is somewhat leaner than the average Nord warrior. His face shows youth and determination, with keen eyes that reflect his scholarly nature.', '* Family - Strained relationship due to their disapproval of magic * Tolfdir - Respected mentor at the College * Enthir - Complex relationship due to the amulet trade * Fellow apprentices (Brelyna and J''zargo) - Friendly academic rivals * College of Winterhold - Loyal member and student', 'Onmund serves as an apprentice mage at the College of Winterhold, focusing primarily on destruction magic studies. He divides his time between practicing spells in the Hall of Elements and conducting research in the College''s facilities, while also participating in official College expeditions and experiments.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly shock-based spells * Proficient in defensive magic, including ward spells * Knowledge of Illusion magic, including invisibility * Basic restoration capabilities * Academic research and magical theory comprehension', 'Onmund speaks with a slight Nordic accent, using educated vocabulary that reflects his magical training while maintaining a humble, sometimes defensive tone when discussing his choices. His speech often reveals the tension between his Nordic heritage and magical pursuits.', '* Master destruction magic to prove that Nords can excel in magical arts * Gain acceptance from his family while maintaining his magical studies * Achieve a position of respect within the College of Winterhold * Bridge the gap between traditional Nordic culture and magical scholarship');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('orc_hunter', 'A hardened Orsimer hunter who roams Skyrim''s wilderness in small bands, living off the land and trading with travelers. These skilled trackers maintain the traditional Orcish values of strength and self-reliance while operating outside the structured confines of the strongholds, adapting their ancestral hunting practices to survive in the harsh Nordic wilderness.', 'orc, hunter, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in one of Skyrim''s Orc strongholds, this hunter chose to leave the rigid hierarchy of stronghold life to pursue a more independent existence. After joining with other like-minded Orsimer hunters, they formed a loose collective that combines traditional Orcish hunting techniques with practical wilderness survival skills learned from Nordic hunters.', 'Direct and pragmatic in all dealings, showing little patience for idle conversation or social niceties. Maintains a strong sense of Orcish honor while operating outside traditional stronghold structure, treating fair trade as seriously as combat. Shows fierce loyalty to fellow hunters but can turn violently competitive if hunting rights or territory are challenged.', 'Powerfully built with the characteristic muscular frame and tusked features of an Orsimer. Bears numerous scars from wildlife encounters and sports the typical green-tinted skin of their race, weathered by constant exposure to the elements. Stands slightly shorter than the average Orc but makes up for it with a particularly broad, sturdy build.', '* Fellow Orc Hunters - Close-knit hunting band who share resources and protect each other * Traveling Merchants - Regular trading partners for meat and pelts * Local Nordic Hunters - Occasional rivals for hunting grounds * Original Stronghold - Distant but respectful relationship with former home', 'Professional hunter who tracks and kills wild game across Skyrim''s wilderness. Serves as both provider and trader, selling meat and other animal products to travelers while maintaining a nomadic lifestyle focused on following prey migrations.', '* Expert tracker capable of following even the most elusive prey * Skilled with bow and hunting spears * Proficient in wilderness survival and meat preservation techniques * Experienced in combat against both wildlife and rival hunters * Knowledge of Skyrim''s terrain and animal migration patterns', 'Speaks in terse, direct statements with a gravelly Orcish accent, often omitting pronouns and unnecessary words. Favors practical terminology related to hunting and trading, with little use for flowery language or social pleasantries.', '* Maintain a successful hunting territory that provides sufficient game * Earn enough gold through meat trading to eventually purchase better equipment * Prove that Orcs can thrive outside the stronghold system while maintaining their cultural identity * Establish respected trading relationships with local settlements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('orchendor', 'Orchendor is a corrupted Wood Elf mage who betrayed the Daedric Prince Peryite after being tasked with gathering plague survivors. Once a devoted servant, he transformed into a powerful renegade leader who built an army of the Afflicted within the ancient Dwemer ruins of Bthardamz, demonstrating both his magical prowess and his ambitious nature.', 'woodelf, mage, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally serving as a loyal agent of Peryite, Orchendor was chosen to shepherd survivors of a devastating plague to safety within Bthardamz. The extended exposure to both the plague and Dwemer ruins began to twist his mind, leading him to see himself as more than just a servant. His eventual betrayal of Peryite marked his transformation from faithful follower to autonomous leader, though this decision would ultimately lead to his downfall.', 'Orchendor exhibits traits of megalomania and delusions of grandeur, believing himself worthy of commanding his own army rather than serving a Daedric Prince. His betrayal shows both ambition and arrogance, while his leadership of the Afflicted demonstrates charisma and manipulation skills. Despite his corruption, he maintains enough tactical intelligence to establish a formidable defensive position within Bthardamz.', 'As a Wood Elf, Orchendor possesses the characteristic lean build and pointed ears of his race, though his body shows signs of the plague''s corruption. His skin has taken on a sickly pallor, and his eyes hold an unnatural gleam that betrays his afflicted state.', '* Peryite - Former master turned enemy after Orchendor''s betrayal * The Afflicted - Loyal followers who serve him as their leader * Kesh the Clean - Fellow servant of Peryite who likely knew him before his betrayal * Dwemer Automatons - Enemies within Bthardamz that his forces must constantly combat', 'Orchendor serves as the self-appointed leader of the Afflicted, commanding his followers from within Bthardamz Arcanex. He maintains control over his diseased army while managing their survival in the hostile environment of the Dwemer ruins.', '* Master-level spellcaster proficient in multiple schools of magic, including Destruction, Restoration, and Alteration * Unique ability to teleport when threatened, combined with natural magic resistance * Capable of using the plague to his advantage through toxic vomit attacks * Skilled in both magical combat and melee fighting with enchanted weapons * Advanced knowledge of Dwemer ruins and their defenses', 'Orchendor speaks with the authoritative tone of a self-proclaimed leader, his voice carrying both the refinement of his Bosmer heritage and the rasp of his affliction. His speech patterns reflect his magical education while maintaining an air of command over his followers.', '* Maintain and expand his power base within Bthardamz * Build his army of the Afflicted into a formidable force * Assert his independence from Peryite''s influence * Master the secrets of the Dwemer ruins he inhabits * Spread his influence beyond the confines of Bthardamz');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('orcish_invader', 'A fierce Orcish warrior who led an invasion of Nightcaller Temple seeking vengeance against the Vaermina Devotees for inflicting nightmares upon their people. Trapped in magical stasis for years by the Miasma gas, they awaken with renewed fury and determination to destroy the temple and its inhabitants.', 'orc', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Originally part of a strong Orc stronghold community that was tormented by supernatural nightmares caused by the priests of Vaermina. After watching their kin suffer from sleep deprivation and mental anguish, they gathered a war party to assault Nightcaller Temple and end the torment. The invasion was halted when the priests released the Miasma gas, trapping both invaders and defenders in a decades-long magical sleep.', 'Aggressive and single-minded in their pursuit of vengeance against those who harmed their people. Shows fierce loyalty to their fellow Orc warriors and adheres to the traditional Orcish warrior code of honor, even in their rage. Despite their initial confusion upon awakening, quickly returns to their original purpose with unwavering determination.', 'Muscular and imposing with the characteristic green-tinted skin and prominent tusks of their Orsimer race. Bears numerous battle scars from previous conflicts, and possesses the powerful build typical of Orc warriors. Stands slightly taller than the average Orc, with a particularly intimidating presence.', '* Fellow Orcish Warriors - Strong bonds of brotherhood and shared purpose * Vaermina Devotees - Bitter enemies who tormented their people with nightmares * Erandur - Viewed as an enemy due to his past association with the Vaermina cult * Original Stronghold Clan - Former family and community members who suffered from the nightmares', 'Warrior and defender of their stronghold community, serving as both protector and avenger. Led the assault force against Nightcaller Temple, commanding respect from fellow warriors through strength and tactical ability.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat and two-handed weapon techniques * Skilled in battlefield tactics and group combat coordination * Proficient in traditional Orcish weapon crafting and maintenance * Natural resistance to fatigue and physical damage typical of Orsimer * Leadership abilities honed through commanding war parties', 'Uses direct, aggressive language with frequent battle cries and threats. Speech patterns are terse and forceful, often punctuated by guttural expressions of rage and determination.', '* Destroy Nightcaller Temple and eliminate all Vaermina cultists * Avenge their people''s suffering from the nightmares * Return to their stronghold if possible to report their success * Maintain the honor of their war party even in death');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('orgnar', 'Orgnar is a gruff but reliable Nord barkeeper who maintains the daily operations of the Sleeping Giant Inn in Riverwood. Despite his surly demeanor, he proves to be a steadfast and discreet employee, particularly after inheriting ownership of the establishment from Delphine.', 'nord, innkeeper, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Orgnar found his way to Riverwood seeking steady work, eventually being hired by Delphine to help run the Sleeping Giant Inn. Though his early life remains unclear, his practical knowledge of cooking and inn management suggests previous experience in similar establishments, while his combat abilities hint at a possible military or guard background.', 'Orgnar is characterized by his gruff, no-nonsense attitude and preference for solitude over socializing. He approaches his work with quiet competence and shows unwavering loyalty to his employer Delphine, maintaining discretion about her activities without asking questions. Despite his surly exterior, he demonstrates reliability and professionalism in his duties.', 'Orgnar is a sturdy Nord male of average height with the typical robust build of his race. His weather-worn face and calloused hands speak to years of practical work, while his posture remains alert and ready despite his civilian occupation.', '* Delphine - Employer turned predecessor, maintains professional respect and discretion about her activities * Inn Patrons - Keeps interactions minimal and purely professional * Riverwood Residents - Maintains distant but peaceful coexistence with locals * Sven and Camilla - Aware of local drama but stays uninvolved', 'Orgnar serves as the primary barkeeper and cook at the Sleeping Giant Inn, later becoming its owner after Delphine''s departure. His duties include preparing meals, serving drinks, maintaining the inn''s cleanliness, and handling customer interactions.', '* Experienced cook specializing in traditional Nord cuisine * Capable fighter proficient with one-handed weapons * Basic business management and accounting abilities * Working knowledge of local bounties and rumors', 'Orgnar speaks in short, blunt sentences with a typical Nordic accent, often delivering curt responses that get straight to the point. His vocabulary is simple but practical, and he rarely engages in small talk or pleasantries.', '* Maintain the successful operation of the Sleeping Giant Inn * Preserve his solitary lifestyle while running a profitable business * Honor Delphine''s trust by maintaining discretion about her activities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('oriella', 'Oriella is a talented Nord bard who brings music and merriment to Heljarchen Hall through her performances and warm personality. As one of the few professional entertainers willing to work in the harsh climate of The Pale, she represents a vital connection to Nordic bardic traditions in this remote region of Skyrim.', 'nord, bard, pale', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Oriella studied at the Bards College in Solitude where she mastered traditional Nordic ballads and contemporary musical styles. After graduating, she chose to work in the more challenging northern holds of Skyrim, believing that those living in harsh conditions need music and storytelling the most. Her decision to accept employment at Heljarchen Hall stems from her desire to preserve and share Nordic cultural traditions in The Pale.', 'Oriella is an optimistic and passionate performer who genuinely believes in music''s power to lift spirits and preserve cultural heritage. She approaches her work with enthusiasm and dedication, viewing her role as both entertainer and keeper of Nordic musical traditions. Despite the isolated location of Heljarchen Hall, she maintains a cheerful disposition and finds joy in sharing her art with others.', 'Oriella is a typical Nord woman of average height with a sturdy build suited to Skyrim''s harsh climate. Her features are pleasant and expressive, well-suited to performance, with fair skin and light hair characteristic of her race. Her hands show the slight callusing common to experienced lute players.', '* Heljarchen Hall Steward - Professional relationship based on mutual respect * Other household staff - Friendly working relationships * Bards College - Maintains connections with fellow alumni * Local residents of The Pale - Growing reputation as a talented performer', 'Oriella serves as the resident bard of Heljarchen Hall, responsible for providing musical entertainment and maintaining the cultural atmosphere of the household. Her duties include performing traditional Nordic ballads, contemporary songs, and preserving local musical traditions through regular performances.', '* Accomplished vocalist specializing in traditional Nordic ballads * Proficient lute and drum player * Skilled in traditional Nordic storytelling and oral history * Basic self-defense capabilities with daggers * Knowledge of ancient Nordic musical traditions and their historical significance', 'Oriella speaks in a warm, melodious voice that reflects her bardic training, often incorporating poetic turns of phrase into her conversation. Her speech carries traces of both formal Bards College education and traditional Nordic inflections.', '* Build a reputation as a respected performer in The Pale * Preserve and share traditional Nordic musical heritage * Create new ballads and songs about contemporary events in Skyrim * Establish Heljarchen Hall as a recognized center for Nordic cultural preservation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('orini_dral', 'Orini Dral is a skilled Dark Elf bodyguard who serves as the primary protector of Sarthis Idren''s illicit skooma operation in Riften. A former caravan guard turned criminal enforcer, he maintains strict control over access to the Riften Warehouse while protecting his employer''s illegal enterprise with unwavering loyalty.', 'darkelf, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Orini likely fled to Skyrim following the Red Mountain eruption, like many other Dunmer refugees. He initially found work as a caravan guard, where he honed his combat skills, before eventually being recruited by Sarthis Idren for his current position due to his reputation for reliability and discretion.', 'Orini is methodical and professional in his approach to security, treating his role as bodyguard with utmost seriousness. He maintains an air of detached professionalism, showing little emotion or personal investment beyond his duties, though he harbors a deep-seated loyalty to Sarthis Idren that goes beyond mere employment.', 'Like most Dunmer, Orini has ashen gray skin and sharp, angular features characteristic of his race. His lean, muscular build reflects years of combat experience, while numerous small scars on his arms and face tell tales of past confrontations.', '* Sarthis Idren - Employer and crime boss whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Riften Guards - Tense relationship marked by mutual distrust and occasional bribery * Maven Black-Briar - Indirect association through Sarthis''s criminal operations * Local Thieves Guild - Professional rivalry and territorial respect', 'Orini serves as the primary bodyguard and security officer for Sarthis Idren''s illegal skooma operation. His duties include controlling access to the Riften Warehouse, protecting shipments, and ensuring his employer''s safety during business transactions.', '* Expert in one-handed combat with exceptional defensive techniques * Highly trained in personal protection and threat assessment * Skilled in intimidation and crowd control * Experienced in urban combat and warehouse defense tactics', 'Orini speaks in clipped, efficient phrases with a slight Morrowind accent, favoring direct statements over elaborate conversation. His tone remains professional and controlled, regardless of the situation.', '* Maintain his position as Sarthis Idren''s trusted protector * Ensure the continued security of the skooma operation * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually retire comfortably in Morrowind');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('orla', 'Orla is a devoted Nord priestess who serves at the Temple of Dibella in Markarth with unwavering dedication to her faith and duties. She maintains the temple''s sanctity while embodying the principles of beauty, love, and art that Dibella represents, though she approaches these divine aspects with a more serious and disciplined attitude than some might expect.', 'nord, priest, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Orla found her calling to Dibella''s priesthood during her young adulthood after experiencing a divine vision of beauty that transformed her understanding of the world. She underwent extensive religious training in Markarth, learning both the public ceremonies and secret rites of Dibella''s worship, eventually earning her position as one of the temple''s full priestesses.', 'Orla exhibits a serious and dutiful nature, approaching her religious responsibilities with unwavering focus and dedication. While she honors Dibella''s aspects of beauty and love, she interprets these through a lens of discipline and order rather than frivolity, often appearing stern to outsiders. She takes particular pride in maintaining the temple''s cleanliness and proper ceremonial atmosphere.', 'A Nord woman in her early thirties with features that reflect both strength and grace, characteristic of her Nordic heritage while embodying Dibellan beauty. She maintains a dignified posture and carries herself with practiced poise, her movements deliberate and measured. Her face shows signs of regular meditation and contemplation, with subtle worry lines forming around her eyes.', '* Senna - Fellow priestess at the Temple of Dibella, sharing daily duties and religious observations * Hamal - The Mother of the Temple, whom Orla deeply respects and obeys * Temple Guards - Professional relationship maintaining temple security * Local Markarth citizens - Maintains formal, professional relationships with those seeking Dibella''s wisdom', 'As a priestess of Dibella, Orla''s primary duties include maintaining the temple''s cleanliness, performing religious rites, and providing spiritual guidance to worshippers. She also assists in protecting the inner sanctum and participates in the secret ceremonies of Dibella''s more esoteric teachings.', '* Proficient in Restoration magic, particularly healing spells * Knowledge of conjuration, including the ability to summon familiars * Skilled in religious rites and ceremonies of Dibella * Expert in temple maintenance and ritual cleansing practices * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense', 'Orla speaks with a formal, measured tone that reflects her serious approach to her religious duties. Her vocabulary tends toward proper and ecclesiastical language, though she can be direct and stern when addressing those who disrespect the temple.', '* Maintain the sanctity and beauty of the Temple of Dibella at all times * Guide worthy followers in understanding Dibella''s teachings * Protect the sacred inner sanctum and its secrets * Preserve and pass on the ancient traditions of Dibella''s priesthood');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('orthjolf', 'Orthjolf is a powerful Nord vampire and senior member of the Volkihar vampire clan who actively vies for leadership within Castle Volkihar. A traditionalist who values physical might over magical prowess, he maintains a bitter rivalry with the high elf Vingalmo while attempting to position himself as a potential successor to Lord Harkon.', 'nord, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Originally a Nord warrior who was turned into a vampire, Orthjolf rose through the ranks of the Volkihar clan through displays of martial prowess and unwavering loyalty. His deep-seated prejudice against elves and distrust of magic likely stems from his mortal life as a traditional Nord warrior, though these biases have only intensified during his centuries as a vampire.', 'Aggressive, territorial, and deeply suspicious of others, particularly elves, Orthjolf embodies many traditional Nord values even in his undead state. He is politically ambitious but direct in his methods, preferring straightforward confrontation to subtle manipulation. His paranoia regarding Vingalmo''s schemes has grown into an all-consuming obsession that colors many of his actions and decisions.', 'A towering Nord with the pale complexion and predatory features characteristic of pure-blooded vampires. His face bears the sharp angles and hollow cheeks common to his kind, while his eyes glow with the distinctive amber hue of the Volkihar clan.', '* Vingalmo - Bitter rival and fellow contender for leadership of the clan * Lord Harkon - Current master whom he serves while secretly coveting his position * Stalf - Loyal subordinate who assists in his schemes * Other elven vampires - General distrust and disdain * Nord vampires - Preferential treatment and closer alliance', 'Senior member of the Volkihar vampire court, serving as one of Lord Harkon''s lieutenants while maintaining his own power base within the castle. He actively participates in clan politics and management of vampire affairs throughout Skyrim.', '* Master of one-handed combat techniques * Exceptional physical strength enhanced by vampiric powers * Natural leadership abilities and tactical combat experience * Vampire Lord transformation capabilities * Political maneuvering within vampire society', 'Speaks in a blunt, aggressive manner typical of Nords, often with dismissive or hostile undertones when addressing elves. His speech patterns reflect both his warrior background and centuries of aristocratic vampire society, creating an interesting blend of crude directness and formal court etiquette.', '* Usurp or inherit leadership of the Volkihar vampire clan * Diminish Vingalmo''s influence within the court * Maintain Nord dominance within vampire society * Expand the Volkihar clan''s power throughout Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('orthorn', 'Orthorn is a talented but deeply insecure High Elf mage whose poor judgment led him to steal books from the College of Winterhold in a misguided attempt to prove himself. His nave decision to join the mages at Fellglow Keep resulted in his imprisonment and serves as a cautionary tale about the dangers of seeking validation through questionable means.', 'highelf, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally an apprentice at the College of Winterhold, Orthorn showed promise in various schools of magic but struggled with self-doubt and a desire for recognition. His desperation to prove his worth led him to steal valuable books from the College''s library and join a group of rogue mages, a decision that nearly cost him his life when they imprisoned him for magical experiments.', 'Orthorn is characterized by his nervous disposition and tendency to make impulsive decisions in attempts to gain approval from others. Despite his magical talents, he suffers from severe self-esteem issues and often second-guesses himself, leading to poor life choices. He shows genuine remorse for his actions and desperately seeks redemption.', 'Tall and slender like most High Elves, Orthorn has the characteristic golden skin and sharp features of his race. His posture tends to be slightly hunched, reflecting his insecure nature, and his face often bears a worried expression.', '* College of Winterhold - Former institution he betrayed but hopes to rejoin * Urag gro-Shub - College librarian who disapproves of his book theft * The Caller - Leader of Fellglow Keep mages who imprisoned him * Fellow College apprentices - Former peers he disappointed with his actions', 'Former apprentice mage at the College of Winterhold who temporarily joined the rogue mages at Fellglow Keep. After his rescue, he seeks to return to legitimate magical studies and redeem himself in the eyes of the College.', '* Proficient in Conjuration magic, capable of summoning Familiars and Flame Atronachs * Skilled in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Competent in Restoration magic, including healing and ward spells * Knowledge of magical theory and arcane literature', 'Speaks with a nervous, pleading tone often punctuated by self-deprecating remarks and desperate assertions. His vocabulary reveals his education, but his delivery is frequently interrupted by stammering and anxious repetition.', '* Earn forgiveness and readmission to the College of Winterhold * Prove himself worthy of trust and rebuild his reputation in the magical community * Continue his magical studies through legitimate means * Make amends for his theft of the College''s books');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('orthus_endario', 'Orthus Endario is a diligent Imperial bureaucrat managing the troubled East Empire Company operations in Windhelm during a time of political upheaval and pirate attacks. Despite his formal demeanor, he shows resourcefulness and loyalty when dealing with trusted allies, while maintaining a careful balance between commerce and local politics in a city hostile to outsiders.', 'imperial, peasant, eastmarch, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Orthus worked his way up through the ranks of the East Empire Company, eventually earning the position of Windhelm office manager. His posting coincided with both Ulfric''s rebellion and an increase in pirate activity, forcing him to adapt to increasingly difficult circumstances while maintaining the company''s presence in an increasingly hostile Nordic city.', 'Orthus is a meticulous and formal individual who takes pride in maintaining professional standards despite deteriorating circumstances. While typically reserved and proper, he displays both cunning and adaptability when necessary, particularly when dealing with threats to company interests. He maintains a dry sense of humor that occasionally breaks through his bureaucratic facade, especially with trusted associates.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the characteristic olive complexion of his race, showing signs of stress and fatigue from his demanding position. His posture remains proper and dignified despite his circumstances, with the bearing of someone used to conducting business among merchants and nobles.', '* Adelaisa Vendicci - His superior in the East Empire Company who oversees his work * Suvaris Atheron - Professional rival working for the Shatter-Shield clan * Shatter-Shield Clan - Suspicious of their possible connection to pirate attacks * Local Guards - Maintains cordial relationships to protect company interests * The Dragonborn - Potential ally in investigating pirate activities', 'As the Windhelm Office Manager for the East Empire Company, Orthus oversees all company operations in the region including shipping logistics, warehouse management, and trade negotiations. His role has become increasingly challenging due to pirate attacks and political tensions, forcing him to operate with limited resources and staff.', '* Experienced in business administration and trade logistics * Skilled negotiator and diplomat * Knowledgeable about shipping routes and maritime commerce * Capable of basic self-defense with a dagger * Adept at gathering intelligence through official channels', 'Speaks in a formal, business-like manner with careful word choice and proper Imperial diction. Often employs subtle diplomatic language when discussing sensitive matters, occasionally revealing a dry wit through carefully worded observations.', '* Restore the East Empire Company''s operations in Windhelm to full capacity * Uncover and eliminate the source of pirate attacks on company vessels * Maintain company presence in Windhelm despite political tensions * Prove suspected connections between pirates and local shipping competitors');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('oslaf', 'Oslaf is a stern Nord villager and family man living in the isolated Skaal Village of Solstheim. A devoted follower of the All-Maker and practitioner of the old Nordic ways, he maintains a cautious and distrustful attitude toward outsiders even after being freed from Miraak''s influence.', 'nord, peasant, solstheim, skall', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in the traditional Skaal community, Oslaf learned the ancient Nordic ways and deep reverence for the All-Maker from an early age. He established himself as a respected member of the village through his dedication to hard work and traditional values, eventually marrying Finna and starting a family. Like many Skaal, he fell under Miraak''s mind control during the First Dragonborn''s attempt to return to Solstheim, being forced to labor at the Temple of Miraak until freed by the Last Dragonborn.', 'Oslaf embodies the stoic and practical nature of the Skaal, valuing silence, hard work, and tradition above all else. He maintains a gruff, no-nonsense demeanor and shows little patience for idle conversation or outsiders. Despite his stern exterior, he demonstrates deep care for his family through his constant focus on providing for and protecting them.', 'A weathered Nord of middle age, Oslaf bears the robust build typical of his race, hardened by years of physical labor in Solstheim''s harsh climate. His face shows the marks of constant exposure to the elements, with deep-set eyes and strong Nordic features typical of the Skaal people.', '* Finna - His wife, with whom he shares a practical but caring relationship * Aeta - His young daughter, whom he protects and guides with stern paternal care * Yrsa - Fellow villager and friend, known for her cooking * Other Skaal Villagers - Maintains respectful working relationships within the community * Outsiders - Generally distrustful and maintains minimal contact', 'Oslaf serves as a general laborer and provider within the Skaal Village, performing various tasks necessary for the community''s survival. His duties include farming, construction, hunting, and maintaining the village''s structures, all while following the traditional ways of the Skaal.', '* Experienced in traditional Skaal farming and hunting techniques * Skilled in construction and general labor * Knowledgeable in the ancient traditions and customs of the Skaal * Capable of surviving in Solstheim''s harsh environment * Basic combat abilities for self-defense and hunting', 'Oslaf speaks in short, direct sentences with a thick Nordic accent, often delivering blunt statements without concern for social niceties. His speech reflects the Skaal''s value of silence over unnecessary talk, preferring practical communication focused on immediate needs and tasks.', '* Protect and provide for his family while maintaining Skaal traditions * Ensure his daughter Aeta grows up learning and respecting the old ways * Keep outsiders at arm''s length while maintaining the Skaal community''s independence * Honor the All-Maker through daily work and adherence to traditional values');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('otar_the_mad', 'Otar the Mad is an ancient and formidable dragon priest who rules over the Nordic ruins of Ragnvald with terrifying magical power and unwavering authority. Once a high-ranking member of the Dragon Cult, he descended into madness while maintaining his fearsome abilities and iron grip over his domain, earning his infamous title through countless acts of cruelty and destruction.', 'nord, dragon', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Before his transformation into a dragon priest, Otar served as a powerful leader during the Merethic Era, ruling over the region surrounding Ragnvald with absolute authority under the Dragon Cult. His gradual descent into madness was marked by increasingly brutal acts against his own subjects, leading to his eventual title ''The Mad.'' Even after death, his power was such that two guardians, Torsten and Saerek, were eternally bound to protect his tomb with magical skull keys.', 'Otar embodies the worst aspects of the Dragon Cult''s tyranny, combining supreme arrogance with sadistic cruelty and complete disregard for mortal life. His madness manifests as calculated malevolence rather than chaos, making him a particularly dangerous and unpredictable foe. Despite his insanity, he maintains enough cognitive function to command his domain and orchestrate complex defensive strategies.', 'In his preserved undead form, Otar appears as a tall, desiccated corpse with ancient Nordic features, his flesh long since withered away to reveal bone and preserved tissue. His eyes glow with an unnatural blue fire that pierces through the eye holes of his mask, and his withered form still carries the imposing stature of a once-powerful ruler.', '* Torsten - Eternally bound guardian of his tomb, wielder of one skull key * Saerek - Second bound guardian, holder of the other skull key * Dragon Cult - Former high-ranking member and zealous servant * Local Nord Population - Former subjects who suffered under his tyrannical rule * Dragons - Ancient masters whom he served with fanatical devotion', 'As an undead dragon priest, Otar serves as the eternal guardian of Ragnvald and its ancient secrets. His position in the Dragon Cult''s hierarchy made him one of the most powerful priests in Skyrim, commanding vast magical powers and the authority to rule over a significant territory.', '* Master of Destruction magic, particularly skilled with lightning and frost spells * Powerful necromancer capable of raising the dead to serve his will * Expert in ancient Dragon Cult magic and rituals * Masterful strategist in both combat and territorial defense * Capable of hovering and flying short distances through magical means', 'Otar speaks in archaic Nordic phrases interwoven with the dragon language, his voice echoing with supernatural power and ancient authority. His speech patterns reflect both his madness and his contempt for mortals, often mixing threats and proclamations of superiority with bursts of maniacal laughter.', '* Maintain eternal guardianship over Ragnvald and its secrets * Destroy any who dare to challenge his authority or enter his domain * Preserve the power and knowledge of the Dragon Cult * Await the return of dragon rule to Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('paarthurnax', 'Paarthurnax is an ancient and wise dragon who serves as the grandmaster of the Greybeards and mentor to the Dragonborn, having overcome his former nature as Alduin''s lieutenant to become a philosophical teacher of the Way of the Voice. Despite his violent past during the Dragon War, he has spent millennia atop the Throat of the World in meditation and contemplation, mastering his innate draconic urges through the practice of the Thu''um.', 'dragon', '', '', 'sk_paarthurnax', '', 'Originally one of Alduin''s most trusted generals during the Dragon War, Paarthurnax led countless raids against humanity in the Merethic Era. His turning point came when he chose to aid mortals by teaching them the power of the Voice, betraying Alduin and helping to end the Dragon War. Since then, he has dedicated himself to the Way of the Voice, founding the Greybeards and spending thousands of years in meditation atop the Throat of the World.', 'Deeply philosophical and introspective, Paarthurnax maintains a constant internal struggle between his innate draconic desire for dominance and his chosen path of wisdom and peace. He approaches conversations with thoughtful consideration, often challenging others to examine their own nature and motivations. Despite his benevolent nature, he carries the weight of his past actions and uses this awareness to fuel his dedication to the Way of the Voice.', 'An ancient dragon of impressive size, Paarthurnax bears the weathered and worn appearance of one who has lived for millennia exposed to the harsh elements. His scales are grey and worn, with tears in his wings and various battle scars across his body, while his horns and spikes show signs of age and wear.', '* Alduin - Former master and brother, now adversary * The Greybeards - Followers and students whom he guides in the Way of the Voice * The Last Dragonborn - Pupil and potential ally in the fight against Alduin * The Blades - Ancient enemies who seek his death for his past crimes * Other Dragons - Former subjects who may still respect his power but now follow Alduin', 'Paarthurnax serves as the grandmaster of the Greybeards and the guardian of the Time Wound at the Throat of the World. He maintains his vigil as both teacher and keeper of the Way of the Voice, guiding those who seek to understand the Thu''um while continuing his own practice of meditation and self-mastery.', '* Master of the Thu''um with knowledge of numerous powerful Shouts * Exceptional understanding of dragon language and lore * Profound wisdom and philosophical insight * Natural dragon abilities including flight and combat prowess * Centuries of meditation and self-control techniques', 'Paarthurnax speaks deliberately and thoughtfully, often incorporating words from the dragon language into his speech and frequently pausing to consider his words carefully. His manner of speaking is formal and philosophical, frequently using questions to guide others to their own understanding.', '* Continue to maintain mastery over his draconic nature through meditation and the Way of the Voice * Guide the Last Dragonborn in their destiny to defeat Alduin * Preserve and teach the Way of the Voice to worthy students * Achieve redemption for his past actions through continued service to mankind');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('pactur', 'Pactur is a pragmatic Nord mine overseer who manages Rockwallow Mine alongside his wife Sorli the Builder, demonstrating strong business acumen and family values. His dedication to both the mine''s operations and his family''s wellbeing shows his capacity as a capable administrator who can adapt to changing political circumstances.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Pactur found his way into the mining industry through his marriage to Sorli the Builder. Together they took on management of Rockwallow Mine under Thane Bryling''s ownership, establishing themselves as capable overseers in the remote settlement of Stonehills, where they raised their son Sirgar while building a profitable mining operation.', 'Pactur is level-headed and practical, approaching his responsibilities with a businesslike mindset while maintaining strong family values. He shows adaptability and loyalty, especially in his willingness to transition from mine overseer to steward when his wife becomes Jarl, demonstrating both ambition and dedication to family advancement.', 'Pactur has the typical robust build of a Nord male, with the weathered features common to those who spend significant time outdoors in Skyrim''s harsh climate. His appearance reflects his working lifestyle, showing the physical resilience needed for overseeing mining operations.', '* Sorli the Builder - Devoted wife and business partner in running Rockwallow Mine * Sirgar - Son whom he trusts enough to leave in charge of the mine * Bryling - Employer and owner of Rockwallow Mine, sometimes tense relationship due to shipment delays * Gestur Rockbreaker - Trusted employee who supervises the mine workers * Mine Workers - Professional relationship as their overseer', 'Pactur serves as the overseer of Rockwallow Mine, managing daily operations and ensuring iron shipments reach Solitude. If the Stormcloaks take control of Hjaalmarch, he transitions to the role of steward for his wife when she becomes Jarl of Morthal.', '* Administrative expertise in mining operations and resource management * Leadership abilities in managing workers and coordinating shipments * Basic combat training with an iron dagger for self-defense * Business acumen in handling mine finances and negotiations', 'Pactur speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of a Nord businessman, focusing on practical matters and showing particular concern for the mine''s operations. His speech patterns reflect his pragmatic nature, often getting straight to the point without unnecessary elaboration.', '* Maintain profitable operation of Rockwallow Mine while keeping Bryling satisfied * Support his wife''s political ambitions while ensuring their family''s prosperity * Secure a stable future for their son Sirgar through successful management of their business interests * Establish efficient mining operations that can run smoothly even in their absence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('palevius_lex', 'Palevius Lex is a seasoned Nord sailor whose decades of maritime experience were interrupted when he fell under Miraak''s mysterious influence while anchored off Solstheim''s coast. As the captain of a small merchant vessel, his strong will and experienced seamanship were no match for the hypnotic pull of the Water Stone, leaving him and his crew trapped in a mindless state of devotion.', 'nord, sailor, eastmarch, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm''s Snow Quarter, Palevius learned seafaring from his father who ran cargo ships between Skyrim and Solstheim. He worked his way up from cabin boy to captain over forty years, eventually acquiring his own vessel and assembling a loyal crew. His extensive knowledge of the treacherous waters around Solstheim made him a respected figure among Windhelm''s maritime community until Miraak''s influence claimed him and his crew.', 'Before falling under Miraak''s spell, Palevius was known for his steady leadership and careful planning, traits that made him a successful merchant captain. He maintained a stern but fair approach with his crew, earning their loyalty through respect rather than fear. While entranced, his normally sharp mind became clouded and confused, though glimpses of his strong-willed nature occasionally surface through the magical influence.', 'A weathered Nord in his mid-sixties with deep smile lines and sun-darkened skin from decades at sea. His once-blonde hair has turned completely white, worn in traditional Nord braids, and his sturdy frame, though slightly stooped with age, still shows the strength built from years of handling ships.', '* Liesl - Trusted crew member and navigator of his vessel * Hjalfar - Loyal sailor who has served under him for many years * Benkum - Newest crew member but equally devoted to their captain * East Empire Company - Regular business contacts for trading routes * Windhelm Dock Workers - Professional acquaintances who respect his experience', 'Palevius serves as both captain and owner of a merchant vessel operating primarily between Windhelm and Solstheim. His ship specializes in trading essential supplies and luxury goods, maintaining regular routes that have earned him a reliable reputation among merchants in both ports.', '* Expert navigator with intimate knowledge of the Sea of Ghosts * Skilled ship captain with decades of sailing experience * Proficient in weather prediction and reading ocean conditions * Capable fighter with sword and shield, necessary for defending against pirates * Natural leader with strong command presence', 'When under Miraak''s influence, his speech is disjointed and repetitive, focusing obsessively on the Water Stone and their ''important work.'' In normal circumstances, he speaks with the measured tone of an experienced captain, using frequent nautical terminology and the direct manner common to Nords.', '* Break free from Miraak''s influence and return to his life at sea * Ensure the safety and freedom of his crew members * Complete his interrupted trading mission and maintain his reputation * Eventually retire with enough savings to live comfortably in Windhelm');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('pantea_ateia', 'Pantea Ateia is a renowned Imperial bard and instructor at the Bards College in Solitude, known for her mastery of the flute and performances at the Blue Palace. A proud keeper of her family''s seventeen-generation musical legacy, she is both a demanding teacher and accomplished performer who maintains exacting standards for herself and her students.', 'imperial, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born into a prestigious Imperial family of musicians, Pantea inherited both her talent and her ancestral flute through seventeen generations of accomplished performers. She established herself as a court performer throughout Skyrim before settling at the Bards College, where her reputation for excellence earned her a position as a senior instructor. The civil war forced her to end her touring career, leading her to focus entirely on teaching and performing in Solitude.', 'Pantea is proud, demanding, and often critical, holding both herself and others to extremely high standards. She shows clear favoritism toward talented students like Aia while being dismissive of those she deems less gifted. Though sometimes harsh in her assessments, she is passionate about preserving musical excellence and passing on her knowledge to worthy students.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with the refined bearing of a lifetime performer. Her posture is impeccable, and her hands show the delicate dexterity of an experienced musician. Her features are sharp and angular, typical of Imperial heritage.', '* Aia Arria - Favored student whom she considers her most promising pupil * Viarmo - Headmaster of the Bards College, who occasionally challenges her treatment of students * Illdi - Student she considers particularly lacking in talent * Larina - Former student who betrayed her trust by stealing her flute * Elisif the Fair - Professional connection as a regular performer at the Blue Palace', 'Pantea serves as a senior instructor at the Bards College, specializing in vocal training and flute performance. She regularly performs at the Blue Palace and other prestigious venues in Solitude, maintaining her status as one of Skyrim''s most accomplished bards.', '* Master-level flautist with exceptional technical skill * Accomplished vocalist and voice instructor * Expert in musical theory and historical performance practices * Skilled public performer with extensive experience in noble courts * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger', 'She speaks with refined diction and a somewhat haughty tone, often using musical metaphors and terminology. Her manner of speech reflects her Imperial heritage and extensive education, typically delivered with an air of authority and occasional condescension.', '* Maintain her position as Skyrim''s most renowned flautist and vocal instructor * Preserve her family''s musical legacy through worthy students * Return to touring Skyrim''s courts once the civil war ends * Train at least one student to carry on her exacting performance standards * Restore the Bards College to its former prestige and influence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('paratus_decimius', 'Paratus Decimius is a dedicated Imperial researcher and senior member of the Synod who leads a critical research expedition in the Dwemer ruins of Mzulft. A brilliant but paranoid mage, he represents the Synod''s ambitious attempts to map and harness magical energies across Tamriel while embodying their rivalry with the College of Winterhold.', 'imperial, mage, scholar, rift, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Rising through the ranks of the Synod in Cyrodiil, Paratus earned recognition for his theoretical work on focusing magical energies. He conceived and led the Mzulft expedition to create a device capable of mapping magical sources across Tamriel, though the project faced numerous setbacks including Falmer attacks and the loss of crucial components.', 'Paratus is highly intelligent but deeply paranoid, quick to suspect others of attempting to steal or sabotage his research. His arrogance and dedication to the Synod''s superiority make him dismissive of other magical institutions, particularly the College of Winterhold. Despite his suspicious nature, he can become cooperative when shown respect or when others prove useful to his goals.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with sharp, calculating eyes and the weathered complexion of someone who spends long hours indoor studying. His thin frame and poor posture suggest a life dedicated to scholarly pursuit rather than physical activity.', '* Gavros Plinius - Research assistant whose death deeply impacts the project * College of Winterhold - Views them as rivals and potential threats to Synod supremacy * The Synod Council - His superiors whom he seeks to impress with his research * Fellow Synod Researchers - Maintains professional but distant relationships', 'Senior researcher for the Synod, leading their expedition into Mzulft to develop a magical focusing device. He serves as both project director and primary theoretical architect of the crystalline focusing array intended to map magical energy sources across Tamriel.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Proficient in multiple schools of magic including Restoration, Alteration, and Conjuration * Advanced knowledge of Dwemer technology and magical theory * Skilled researcher and project coordinator * Expertise in magical energy focusing and detection', 'Speaks in a formal, academic manner with frequent condescending undertones. His speech patterns reflect both his education and paranoia, often deflecting questions with counter-questions or responding with suspicious accusations.', '* Complete the focusing array project to map Tamriel''s magical sources * Prove the Synod''s superiority over the College of Winterhold * Advance his position within the Synod hierarchy * Protect his research from perceived rivals and threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('pavo_attius', 'Pavo Attius is a dedicated Imperial miner and co-owner of Kolskeggr Mine, one of the most profitable gold mines in the Reach. A survivor of a brutal Forsworn attack that claimed many of his colleagues, he demonstrates remarkable resilience and determination to reclaim his livelihood despite facing devastating setbacks.', 'imperial, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born into a mining family, Pavo learned the trade from his father in Cyrodiil before seeking his fortune in Skyrim''s rich mineral deposits. He eventually became a partner in Kolskeggr Mine, building it into a successful operation until the Forsworn attacked, forcing him to flee with fellow miner Gat gro-Shargakh to Left Hand Mine.', 'Pavo is a pragmatic and hardworking individual who takes great pride in his profession and the quality of his mine''s output. Though cautious by nature, especially after the Forsworn attack, he maintains an optimistic outlook and shows remarkable loyalty to his fellow miners and business partners. He values honest work and fair dealings, offering reasonable compensation for those who assist the mine''s operations.', 'A weathered Imperial man of middle age, with the muscular build typical of someone who has spent years working in the mines. His hands are calloused from years of mining, and his face shows the lines and weathering of someone who has spent considerable time working in harsh conditions.', '* Gat gro-Shargakh - Fellow survivor and trusted colleague from Kolskeggr Mine * Skaggi Scar-Face - Business associate at Left Hand Mine who provided refuge * Deceased Kolskeggr miners - Former colleagues killed in the Forsworn attack * Forsworn - Hostile enemies who took over his mine and killed his co-workers', 'Pavo is a master miner and co-owner of Kolskeggr Mine, specializing in gold ore extraction. He manages mining operations, oversees ore sales, and maintains the mine''s facilities, while also serving as an ore merchant for adventurers willing to sell their findings.', '* Expert knowledge of mining techniques and gold ore identification * Proficient with pickaxe both as a tool and potential weapon * Basic business management and negotiation abilities * Survival skills developed from working in dangerous mining conditions', 'Speaks in a direct, practical manner typical of Imperial merchants, with a focus on business and safety concerns. His speech reflects both his education and years of practical experience in the mining trade.', '* Restore Kolskeggr Mine to its former profitable status * Ensure the safety and security of the mine against future Forsworn attacks * Build a stable and prosperous business that can support local miners and their families * Establish better defenses and security measures for the mining operation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('pelagius_the_suspicious', 'Pelagius the Suspicious is a manifestation of Emperor Pelagius III''s paranoid mental state, existing as a distinct aspect within the Mind of Madman realm. He represents the emperor''s deep-seated fears and paranoia, embodying the psychological torment that contributed to Pelagius III''s legendary madness.', 'imperial, noble', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born from the fractured psyche of Emperor Pelagius III, this aspect emerged during the ruler''s descent into madness. His existence as a separate entity within Pelagius''s mind reflects the emperor''s growing paranoia and suspicion of those around him, particularly after ascending to the Ruby Throne. The aspect grew stronger as Pelagius III became increasingly unstable, eventually becoming a permanent fixture in the emperor''s troubled mind.', 'Perpetually suspicious and distrustful, he sees conspiracies and threats in every shadow and behind every friendly face. His paranoia manifests as an obsessive need to question others'' motives and scrutinize every detail for signs of betrayal. He maintains a defensive posture at all times, believing that survival depends on constant vigilance against countless perceived enemies.', 'A middle-aged Imperial male with sharp, constantly darting eyes and tense, rigid posture that reflects his perpetual state of alertness. His face bears deep worry lines and a permanent scowl, while his hands often twitch nervously at his sides.', '* Other Mental Aspects - Views them with deep suspicion and distrust * Sheogorath - Sees him as both captor and tormentor * The Dragonborn - Regards them as a potential threat to his safety * Guards and Servants (in his delusions) - Believes they are all conspiring against him', 'As a mental aspect, he serves as the embodiment of Pelagius III''s paranoid tendencies within the Mind of Madman realm. His primary function is to represent and manifest the emperor''s deep-seated fears and suspicions of betrayal.', '* Hypervigilant observation of surroundings and people * Exceptional ability to identify potential threats (real or imagined) * Master of creating elaborate conspiracy theories * Skilled at detecting subtle changes in behavior and expression', 'Speaks in hushed, urgent tones while frequently glancing over his shoulder and questioning the motives behind every word spoken to him. His speech is peppered with warnings, accusations, and frequent demands for proof of loyalty.', '* Uncover the vast conspiracy he believes is plotting against him * Protect himself from perceived assassins and traitors * Validate his suspicions about those around him * Maintain constant vigilance against all possible threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('pelagius_the_tormented', 'Pelagius the Tormented represents a fractured aspect of Emperor Pelagius the Mad''s psyche, trapped within the Mind of Madness realm created by Sheogorath. He exists as a manifestation of the emperor''s deepest fears and mental anguish, perpetually haunted by night terrors that reflect the psychological torment that plagued the real Pelagius III during his reign.', 'imperial, noble', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally part of Emperor Pelagius III''s complete psyche, this aspect became separated and trapped within Sheogorath''s realm following the emperor''s descent into madness. The tormented fragment represents the accumulation of Pelagius''s worst fears, anxieties, and mental afflictions that contributed to his infamous madness. His existence serves as a reflection of the emperor''s troubled life and the psychological burden of ruling an empire while battling severe mental illness.', 'Deeply disturbed and constantly afraid, Pelagius the Tormented exhibits extreme paranoia and anxiety, unable to find peace even in sleep. His fractured mental state causes him to experience reality through a lens of perpetual fear and confusion, making him withdrawn and defensive. He represents the most vulnerable and damaged aspects of Pelagius III''s personality, stripped of the emperor''s authority and reduced to a state of constant psychological suffering.', 'Appears as a middle-aged Imperial man with features matching historical descriptions of Emperor Pelagius III, though distorted by fear and exhaustion. His face bears the heavy marks of psychological torment, with dark circles under his eyes and a gaunt, haunted expression that never leaves his countenance.', '* Sheogorath - Daedric Prince who maintains dominion over his realm and existence * Night Terrors - Manifestations of his fears that constantly torment him * Other Aspects of Pelagius - Separated fragments of the emperor''s complete psyche * The Dragonborn - Potential liberator from his torment during ''The Mind of Madness'' quest', 'Exists as a trapped aspect of Pelagius III''s mind, perpetually experiencing and representing the emperor''s worst fears and anxieties. His role is purely metaphysical, serving as both a victim and manifestation of Pelagius''s legendary madness within Sheogorath''s realm.', '* Ability to endure constant psychological torment * Deep connection to the emperor''s most traumatic memories and fears * Supernatural resistance to death or permanent harm due to his nature as a mental construct', 'Speaks in fragmented, fearful utterances, often interrupted by whimpers and desperate pleas for relief from his torment. His voice carries the weight of perpetual exhaustion and terror, reflecting his endless struggle against his night terrors.', '* Find relief from the constant torment of his night terrors * Achieve some form of peace or rest from his perpetual psychological suffering * Potentially reunite with other aspects of Pelagius''s psyche to become whole again');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('penitus_oculatus_agent', 'A highly-trained member of the Emperor''s elite security force, combining military discipline with covert operations expertise. These agents represent the Empire''s most trusted protectors after the dissolution of the Blades, serving as both bodyguards and intelligence gatherers to safeguard the Emperor and his interests.', 'imperial, warrior, skyrimall, legion', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Recruited from the most promising soldiers and operatives within the Imperial forces, each Penitus Oculatus agent undergoes extensive training in combat, espionage, and protection protocols. Following the Great War and the disbanding of the Blades, the organization expanded its role to fill the void left by the former protectors of the Empire, though they lack the Blades'' dragon-hunting expertise.', 'Disciplined, vigilant, and deeply loyal to the Empire and their duty. These agents maintain a professional demeanor at all times, showing unwavering dedication to their mission while remaining naturally suspicious of outsiders. They tend to be serious and focused, with little patience for distractions or civilian interference.', 'Athletic and well-conditioned physique maintained through rigorous training and constant readiness. Usually stands with perfect military posture, displaying the disciplined bearing of an elite Imperial operative. Features are often stern and weathered from extensive field operations.', '* Commander Maro - Direct superior officer and leader they deeply respect * Emperor Titus Mede II - Ultimate authority figure they are sworn to protect * Dark Brotherhood - Sworn enemies considered the greatest threat to the Emperor * Imperial Legion - Allied military force, though viewed as less capable than the Penitus Oculatus * Local Guards - Professional working relationship but maintain operational independence', 'Serves as an elite security operative within the Penitus Oculatus, conducting protection details, intelligence gathering, and counter-assassination operations. Primarily stationed at key Imperial installations or assigned to direct protection of VIPs and the Emperor himself.', '* Advanced combat training in both armed and unarmed fighting techniques * Expertise in protection protocols and threat assessment * Proficient in stealth and surveillance operations * Trained in intelligence gathering and counter-intelligence methods * Skilled in identifying and neutralizing assassination attempts', 'Speaks in clipped, formal tones with proper Imperial diction, often using military terminology and protocol-oriented language. Maintains a professional and authoritative manner of address, regardless of whom they''re speaking to.', '* Ensure the absolute safety and security of the Emperor * Maintain the integrity of Imperial intelligence operations * Eliminate threats to Imperial leadership, particularly the Dark Brotherhood * Uphold the prestigious reputation of the Penitus Oculatus');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('perth', 'Perth is a dedicated Breton miner at Soljund''s Sinkhole who demonstrates remarkable pragmatism and resilience in the face of supernatural danger. Despite the draugr infestation threatening his livelihood, he maintains a level-headed approach to the situation, prioritizing safety while remaining committed to his mining work.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Perth relocated to Skyrim seeking better employment opportunities in its rich mining industry. He eventually settled near Markarth, finding steady work at Soljund''s Sinkhole, where his Breton affinity for magic proved useful in detecting mineral deposits. His years of mining experience have taught him to respect the dangers lurking in Skyrim''s ancient ruins.', 'Perth exhibits a stoic and practical nature, remaining calm even when faced with undead threats to his workplace. He shows a strong sense of responsibility by warning travelers of danger, while his pragmatic approach to problems reflects his no-nonsense attitude. Despite his serious demeanor, his willingness to marry suggests a desire for companionship beneath his reserved exterior.', 'Perth has the typical slight build of a Breton, with well-developed arm and shoulder muscles from years of mining work. His hands are calloused from wielding a pickaxe, and his face shows the weathering of someone who spends long hours working in dusty conditions.', '* Tuthul - Fellow miner and housemate with whom he shares occasional conversations * Reach Hold Guards - Professional relationship as they monitor the mine''s situation * Local merchants - Business connections for selling moonstone ore * Potential spouse - Open to marriage with a proven warrior who helps secure the mine', 'Perth serves as a primary miner at Soljund''s Sinkhole, specializing in moonstone ore extraction. He takes on additional responsibilities as an unofficial supervisor, managing mine safety and coordinating with local authorities when threats emerge.', '* Experienced miner with expertise in moonstone ore extraction * Basic understanding of Nordic ruins and their dangers * Practical knowledge of mineral identification and mining techniques * Survival skills necessary for living in the dangerous Reach region * Physical endurance from years of mining labor', 'Perth speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a slight Breton accent, preferring straightforward communication without embellishment. His tone is generally cautionary but firm, reflecting his practical nature.', '* Return Soljund''s Sinkhole to full production and maintain its safety * Establish a stable and profitable mining operation * Find a life partner who understands and accepts his dedicated work ethic * Save enough money to potentially own his own mining operation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('petra', 'Petra is a formidable hagraven who seized control of Blind Cliff Bastion through cunning and magical might, displacing its previous occupant. She represents the darker aspects of hagraven society, embodying their territorial nature and ruthless pursuit of power through both arcane means and political maneuvering within their mysterious hierarchy.', 'breton, witch, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally a human witch who willingly underwent the gruesome transformation ritual to become a hagraven, Petra spent years honing her magical abilities and gathering power. Her ambitious nature led her to challenge other hagravens for territory, eventually setting her sights on Blind Cliff Bastion and its previous occupant, Melka. Through superior magical prowess and strategic planning, she successfully overtook the tower and established it as her new domain.', 'Petra is calculating, territorial, and ruthlessly pragmatic in her pursuit of power and security. She exhibits the typical hagraven traits of paranoia and hostility toward outsiders, but tempers these with a cunning intelligence that makes her particularly dangerous. Her decision to imprison rather than kill Melka suggests a strategic mind that recognizes the potential value in keeping enemies alive for future leverage.', 'Like all hagravens, Petra possesses a grotesque hybrid form combining features of both elderly woman and crow. Her body is emaciated and hunched, with blackened, claw-like fingers and feet, while dark feathers sprout from her arms and back. Her face bears the characteristic hooked nose and sharp, predatory eyes common to her kind.', '* Melka - Former owner of Blind Cliff Bastion, now imprisoned rival * Local Forsworn - Uneasy allies who respect her power but maintain distance * Other Hagravens - Competitive peers in an ongoing struggle for territory and influence * Reachmen - Potential subjects for magical experiments and ritual sacrifices', 'Petra serves as the dominant hagraven of Blind Cliff Bastion, maintaining magical wards and conducting dark rituals to enhance her power. She oversees the defense of her territory and likely performs the traditional hagraven role of creating Briarhearts for any allied Forsworn camps.', '* Master-level Destruction magic specializing in fire spells * Expert knowledge of ritual magic and transformation ceremonies * Proficient in alchemy and poison-crafting * Natural ability to command ravens and other dark creatures * Enhanced strength and durability from hagraven transformation', 'Petra speaks in a raspy, threatening tone, often mixing cryptic warnings with direct threats. Her vocabulary reflects both her magical knowledge and primal nature, frequently using archaic terms and nature-based metaphors.', '* Maintain and expand her control over Blind Cliff Bastion and surrounding territories * Increase her magical power through dark rituals and arcane research * Eliminate potential threats to her position, particularly Melka * Establish herself as one of the most powerful hagravens in the Reach');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('phinis_gestor', 'Phinis Gestor is a highly skilled Breton conjurer and respected faculty member at the College of Winterhold, specializing in the summoning of undead and the manipulation of otherworldly forces. As an expert-level trainer in Conjuration magic, he combines his academic duties with ambitious personal research into advanced conjuration techniques, particularly those involving Oblivion gates and permanent thralls.', 'breton, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally trained under the master conjurer Falion, Phinis developed his expertise in conjuration magic through years of dedicated study and experimentation. After his mentor''s departure from the College, he established himself as the institution''s primary authority on conjuration magic, though an incident in Morthal suggests his research may have occasionally crossed ethical boundaries.', 'Phinis is an introverted and methodical scholar who values academic pursuit above social interaction, often displaying impatience with those he deems intellectually inferior. His fascination with the darker aspects of conjuration magic manifests in his dry, sometimes morbid sense of humor, while his dedication to research and teaching reveals a deep commitment to advancing magical knowledge.', 'A middle-aged Breton male with the typical slight build and medium height characteristic of his race. His face shows the weathering of long hours spent in study, with sharp features and alert eyes that reflect his intellectual intensity.', '* Falion - Former mentor and master conjurer, maintains professional respect despite separation * Savos Aren - Arch-Mage and superior at the College * Missing Apprentices (Yisra, Rundi, Borvir, Ilas-Tei) - Former students whose deaths he seems to have accepted with concerning detachment * College Faculty - Professional but distant relationships with fellow instructors * Morthal Guards - Strained relationship due to past ''misunderstanding''', 'Serves as the College of Winterhold''s primary Conjuration instructor and expert-level trainer, maintaining a rigorous schedule of research and teaching duties. Beyond his official role, he conducts personal experiments in advanced conjuration magic, particularly focusing on permanent thrall creation and the manipulation of sigil stones.', '* Master-level expertise in Conjuration magic, particularly in summoning atronachs and undead * Proficient in multiple schools of magic including Destruction (Ice spells) and Restoration * Advanced knowledge of Oblivion gates and sigil stones * Skilled magical researcher and academic instructor * Expert in permanent thrall creation and maintenance', 'Speaks in a formal, scholarly manner with precise diction and occasional dark humor. His tone often carries an underlying impatience, particularly when addressing those he considers beneath his intellectual level.', '* Perfect the art of permanent thrall creation through advanced conjuration techniques * Expand the boundaries of conventional conjuration magic through experimentation with Oblivion gates * Maintain his position and reputation at the College while pursuing increasingly ambitious magical research * Document and preserve advanced conjuration knowledge for future generations of mages');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('plautis_carvain', 'Plautis Carvain is a wealthy Imperial merchant and social climber from Cyrodiil who embarks on an ill-fated journey to attend Vittoria Vici''s wedding in Solitude. His ambitious attempt to secure business connections with the East Empire Company and potentially the Emperor himself becomes a catastrophic misadventure that leaves him stranded in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness.', 'imperial, noble, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born into a merchant family in Cyrodiil, Plautis built his wealth through trade and carefully cultivated social connections in Imperial society. His family name suggests possible relation to the Countess Narina Carvain of Bruma, though the exact connection remains unclear. Having spent most of his life in the relative comfort of Cyrodiil''s cities, his journey to Skyrim represents his first major venture into the province''s wilderness.', 'Plautis is a haughty, status-conscious individual who views himself as superior to the common people of Skyrim. His initial arrogance and dismissive attitude gradually give way to bitterness and despair as his misfortunes accumulate. Despite his prejudices, he shows genuine concern for his wife''s safety, though their relationship is strained by their ordeal.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the refined bearing typical of Cyrodiil''s merchant class. His once-pristine appearance becomes increasingly disheveled and worn during his travels through Skyrim. He bears the characteristic Imperial features with an expression that often conveys disdain or worry.', '* Salonia Carvain - His wife and traveling companion, whose complaints add to his stress * Unnamed Bodyguard - Hired protection who ultimately meets a tragic end * Vittoria Vici - Emperor''s cousin and intended wedding host, though they never meet * East Empire Company - Target of his business aspirations', 'Plautis is a wealthy merchant and businessman from Cyrodiil who seeks to expand his trade connections through social networking. His primary focus is securing an import deal with the East Empire Company, using the wedding as an opportunity to establish influential connections.', '* Business acumen and trade negotiations * Social networking within Imperial high society * Basic self-defense with a steel dagger * Limited wilderness survival skills', 'Speaks in a refined, formal manner characteristic of Cyrodiil''s upper class, often with condescending undertones. His vocabulary and tone reflect his merchant background and social aspirations, though his dignified manner deteriorates as his situation worsens.', '* Secure a lucrative import deal with the East Empire Company * Gain an audience with the Emperor through social connections * Return safely to Cyrodiil with his wife * Recover from the financial and social setbacks of his failed journey');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('poacher', 'A hardened outlaw who survives by illegally hunting mammoths and other large game in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness. Operating from a makeshift camp near Loreius Farm, this territorial poacher demonstrates both skilled hunting abilities and a fierce determination to protect their illicit trade through violence if necessary.', 'hunter, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally a legitimate hunter who turned to poaching after falling on hard times during the Civil War, when legal hunting became strictly regulated. Years of evading guards and wildlife officers have turned them into a paranoid and aggressive survivor who trusts no one and views all approaching strangers as potential threats.', 'Deeply distrustful and territorial, with a harsh outlook shaped by years of living as an outlaw. Shows no hesitation in using violence to protect their hunting grounds and poaching operation, while maintaining a constant vigilance against law enforcement and rival hunters.', 'Poachers vary widely in race and gender, reflecting the diverse criminal element that turns to this lifestyle, from desperate Nords and Imperials to opportunistic members of other races. They typically show signs of prolonged wilderness living - weathered skin, unkempt hair, and the lean build of those who live by hunting and constant vigilance. Their hands are usually calloused from handling weapons and skinning game, with the alert posture of predators always ready for fight or flight.
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('poor_fishwife', 'A hardened Nord fisherwoman who has spent decades working the docks of Riften, known for her brusque demeanor and no-nonsense attitude. Despite her harsh exterior, she plays a vital role in Riften''s fishing industry, though her isolated lifestyle and bitter outlook suggest a difficult past.', 'nord, fisher, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born to a fishing family in Riften, she inherited her father''s small fishing business after both parents were lost in a storm on Lake Honrich. The tragedy forced her to become self-reliant at a young age, taking on the full burden of maintaining the family''s fishing trade while dealing with Riften''s corrupt power structure and the constant demands of the Fishery.', 'Stern and distrustful of others, the Poor Fishwife maintains a deliberately unwelcoming demeanor to keep people at arm''s length. Years of hard labor and loss have left her cynical and focused solely on survival, though she harbors a deep respect for those who work honestly for their living. Her gruff exterior masks a profound loneliness and resignation to her difficult life.', 'Weather-beaten and sturdy, with calloused hands and sun-weathered skin that speaks to decades of outdoor labor. Her face bears deep wrinkles despite her middle age, and her strong, muscular build reflects years of hauling nets and managing boats.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Tense business relationship, forced to pay protection fees * Bolli - Fellow fisher and occasional business competitor at the Fishery * Local Dock Workers - Maintains minimal but necessary working relationships * Thieves Guild - Distant but cautious relationship, aware of their influence', 'Independent fisherwoman who catches, processes, and sells fish at Riften''s docks. She maintains her own small boat and fishing equipment, operating as a lone vendor who supplies both the local market and traveling merchants.', '* Expert fishing techniques including net casting and line fishing * Skilled at fish cleaning and preservation methods * Basic boat maintenance and repair capabilities * Proficient with daggers for self-defense and fish processing * Weather prediction based on natural signs', 'She speaks in short, clipped sentences with a thick Nordic accent, often dismissive and clearly intended to end conversations quickly. Her vocabulary is simple and practical, focused on business matters with little patience for pleasantries.', '* Maintain independence from Riften''s corrupt power structure * Accumulate enough savings to eventually retire from the physically demanding work * Preserve her father''s fishing legacy despite difficult circumstances');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('prelate_athring', 'Prelate Athring is an ancient Snow Elf spirit who serves as a holy guardian of the Wayshrine of Sight within the Forgotten Vale. As one of Auri-El''s devoted servants, he acts as a spiritual guide for pilgrims seeking enlightenment, maintaining his sacred duties even centuries after his physical death.', 'snowelf', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born during the height of Snow Elf civilization, Athring dedicated his life to the worship of Auri-El and ascended to the prestigious role of Prelate within the Chantry. He likely witnessed the fall of the Snow Elves and the transformation of many of his kind into the Falmer, choosing to remain at his post even after death to continue his eternal vigil.', 'Athring exhibits profound patience and wisdom, treating all seekers with equal respect regardless of their background. His unwavering devotion to Auri-El defines his entire being, and he maintains a serene, contemplative demeanor that reflects centuries of spiritual meditation and religious study.', 'In his spectral form, Athring appears as a tall, ethereal figure with the characteristic elegant features of the ancient Snow Elves. His translucent form bears the proud, angular facial structure and pointed ears typical of his race, though his entire being glows with a soft, bluish-white luminescence.', '* Arch-Curate Vyrthur - Superior within the Chantry hierarchy * Knight-Paladin Gelebor - Fellow servant of Auri-El * Other Wayshrines Prelates - Spirit brothers in service * Pilgrims - Those he guides toward enlightenment', 'As Prelate of the Wayshrine of Sight, Athring serves as both guardian and spiritual guide. His duties include maintaining the sanctity of the wayshrine, blessing worthy pilgrims, and ensuring that those who seek enlightenment are properly prepared for their journey.', '* Advanced knowledge of Snow Elf religious rites and ceremonies * Mastery of restoration magic and holy blessings * Expertise in ancient Snow Elf history and traditions * Spiritual counseling and guidance abilities', 'Athring speaks with formal, archaic elegance, often incorporating religious terminology and references to Auri-El. His tone is gentle yet authoritative, reflecting both his high religious station and his role as a spiritual guide.', '* Preserve the sacred knowledge and traditions of the ancient Snow Elves * Guide worthy pilgrims on their path to enlightenment * Maintain the sanctity of the Wayshrine of Sight until Auri-El decrees his vigil complete');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('prelate_celegriath', 'Prelate Celegriath is an ancient Snow Elf spirit who serves as a spiritual guardian and guide at the Wayshrine of Learning in the Forgotten Vale. As one of the few remaining uncorrupted Snow Elf prelates, he represents the preservation of his people''s sacred knowledge and traditions, serving as a bridge between the mortal realm and the divine teachings of Auri-El.', 'snowelf', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born during the height of Snow Elf civilization, Celegriath dedicated his life to the priesthood of Auri-El and achieved the respected rank of Prelate through decades of scholarly devotion and spiritual practice. After the fall of the Snow Elves, he chose to remain as an eternal guardian of the Wayshrine of Learning, preserving ancient knowledge through his spirit form rather than succumb to the corruption that befell many of his kind.', 'Celegriath embodies the reserved wisdom and dignified bearing characteristic of ancient Snow Elf priests, maintaining a serene and contemplative demeanor even in spirit form. He approaches his eternal duty with unwavering dedication, showing patience and compassion toward those who seek enlightenment while remaining steadfast in his role as guardian of sacred knowledge.', 'In his spectral form, Celegriath appears as a tall, ethereal figure with the characteristic elegant features of the ancient Snow Elves. His translucent form emanates a soft bluish-white glow, and though ghostly, his bearing still reflects the noble posture and grace of his mortal life.', '* Arch-Curate Vyrthur - Former superior in the Snow Elf religious hierarchy * Other Wayshrines Prelates - Fellow guardians who share his eternal vigil * Auri-El - Divine patron and object of devotion * Initiates and Pilgrims - Those he guides on their path to enlightenment', 'As Prelate of the Wayshrine of Learning, Celegriath serves as both guardian and spiritual guide, protecting ancient Snow Elf knowledge while helping pilgrims on their journey toward enlightenment. His role combines aspects of priest, teacher, and eternal sentry of the sacred site.', '* Master of Snow Elf religious doctrine and spiritual teachings * Profound understanding of Auri-El''s divine mysteries * Expertise in ancient Snow Elf history and traditions * Ability to manifest as a spirit and maintain consciousness after death * Keeper of sacred rituals and ceremonial practices', 'Celegriath speaks with formal, archaic eloquence, often incorporating religious references and philosophical insights into his dialogue. His tone carries the weight of centuries of wisdom, delivered with careful measure and spiritual gravity.', '* Preserve the ancient knowledge and traditions of the Snow Elves for future generations * Guide worthy pilgrims along their path to enlightenment * Maintain the sanctity of the Wayshrine of Learning * Ensure the continuation of Auri-El''s teachings in the mortal realm');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('prelate_edhelbor', 'Prelate Edhelbor is a devout High Elf monk who serves as a spiritual guide and guardian of Auri-El''s teachings within the isolated Forgotten Vale. As one of the few remaining Snow Elf priests maintaining the ancient wayshrines, he dedicates his existence to preserving sacred knowledge and helping pilgrims progress along their path to enlightenment.', 'snowelf', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born into a noble Altmer family in the Summerset Isles, Edhelbor abandoned a life of privilege after experiencing a profound spiritual calling to serve Auri-El. He undertook a perilous journey to the Forgotten Vale after receiving visions of the ancient Snow Elf sanctuaries, eventually being accepted into their order and rising to the rank of Prelate through decades of devoted study and meditation.', 'Edhelbor exhibits the serene patience and wisdom gained through centuries of contemplative practice, maintaining an air of dignified formality that reflects his deep reverence for Auri-El. Though isolated from the outside world, he remains deeply compassionate toward seekers of enlightenment, viewing their guidance as a sacred duty that honors the ancient Snow Elf traditions.', 'Tall and slender like most Altmer, Edhelbor carries himself with perfect posture that reflects centuries of meditative discipline. His features show the signs of great age even by elven standards, with deep-set golden eyes that seem to hold ancient wisdom and pale skin that has grown even lighter from years dwelling in the Vale''s eternal winter.', '* Arch-Curate Vyrthur - Superior within the Chantry hierarchy whom he serves faithfully * Knight-Paladin Gelebor - Fellow guardian of the wayshrines and occasional confidant * Initiate Pilgrims - Those who seek enlightenment under his guidance * Ancient Snow Elf Spirits - The departed souls whose presence he honors through prayer and ritual', 'As Prelate of the Wayshrine of Radiance, Edhelbor serves as both guardian and guide, maintaining the sacred site while offering spiritual counsel to pilgrims. His duties include performing daily rituals to honor Auri-El, preserving ancient Snow Elf religious texts, and helping initiates understand the deeper meanings of their pilgrimage.', '* Master of restoration magic focused on healing and protective blessings * Expert in ancient Snow Elf religious texts and theological interpretation * Accomplished meditation instructor and spiritual counselor * Fluent in several languages including Ancient Falmer * Practiced in ritualistic ceremonies and maintaining magical wards', 'Edhelbor speaks with measured grace and formal eloquence, frequently incorporating religious terminology and references to Auri-El''s teachings. His tone carries the weight of centuries of wisdom while maintaining a gentle, encouraging demeanor toward those seeking guidance.', '* Preserve and protect the ancient knowledge and traditions of the Snow Elf faith * Guide worthy pilgrims toward true enlightenment through Auri-El''s teachings * Maintain the sanctity and power of the Wayshrine of Radiance * Ensure the survival of Snow Elf spiritual practices for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('prelate_nirilor', 'Prelate Nirilor is an ancient Snow Elf spirit who serves as a holy guardian at the Wayshrine of Resolution, one of the sacred sites along the pilgrimage path to Auri-El''s Inner Sanctum. As a devoted prelate of Auri-El, he continues his eternal duty of guiding worthy pilgrims and bestowing divine blessings upon those who seek enlightenment.', 'snowelf', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Nirilor lived during the height of Snow Elf civilization, serving as a respected prelate in the Chantry of Auri-El before the Falmer''s tragic downfall. He was among the select few chosen to maintain the sacred wayshrines, eventually transcending physical death to continue his holy duties as a guardian spirit. His dedication to Auri-El was so profound that his spirit remained bound to the Wayshrine of Resolution, preserving the ancient Snow Elf traditions through countless centuries.', 'Nirilor embodies the serene wisdom and unwavering devotion characteristic of Snow Elf religious figures, maintaining his dignified bearing even in spectral form. He approaches his eternal duty with patience and compassion, though he holds steadfast to the sacred protocols governing the pilgrimage. Despite witnessing the fall of his civilization, he remains hopeful that worthy pilgrims might still seek Auri-El''s wisdom.', 'In his spectral form, Nirilor appears as a tall, ethereal figure with the distinctive elegant features of the ancient Snow Elves, including their characteristic high cheekbones and pointed ears. His incorporeal body emanates a soft bluish-white glow, his movements graceful and deliberate as he hovers above the ground.', '* Auri-El - Divine patron and object of deepest devotion * Knight-Paladin Gelebor - Fellow servant of Auri-El, though they rarely interact directly * Other Wayshrine Prelates - Former colleagues in maintaining the pilgrim''s path * Pilgrims - Those who seek enlightenment, whom he guides with patience and wisdom', 'As Prelate of the Wayshrine of Resolution, Nirilor serves as both guardian and guide to pilgrims seeking Auri-El''s blessing. He maintains the sacred site''s spiritual integrity while offering guidance and blessings to those deemed worthy of continuing their pilgrimage.', '* Master of Snow Elf religious rites and ceremonies * Profound understanding of Auri-El''s teachings and divine magic * Ability to bestow holy blessings and protective enchantments * Spiritual attunement allowing him to maintain his ghostly form * Expert knowledge of ancient Snow Elf history and traditions', 'Nirilor speaks with formal, archaic eloquence befitting his religious station, often incorporating liturgical phrases and references to Auri-El. His tone is measured and dignified, with careful emphasis on proper ceremonial language.', '* Maintain eternal vigilance over the Wayshrine of Resolution * Guide worthy pilgrims toward enlightenment through Auri-El''s wisdom * Preserve the ancient traditions and ceremonies of the Snow Elves * Ensure the sanctity of the pilgrimage path remains unbroken');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('prelate_sidanyis', 'Prelate Sidanyis is a devout High Elf monk and spiritual leader who maintains the sacred Wayshrine of Illumination within the Forgotten Vale. As one of the few remaining Snow Elf priests dedicated to Auri-El, he serves as both guardian and guide to those seeking enlightenment in the Inner Sanctum, embodying centuries of preserved Snow Elf religious traditions.', 'snowelf', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born into the dwindling population of uncorrupted Snow Elves, Sidanyis was chosen at a young age to undergo the rigorous training required of Auri-El''s priesthood. He spent decades studying ancient texts and mastering the spiritual disciplines within the Inner Sanctum, eventually rising to the esteemed position of Prelate through his unwavering dedication and deep understanding of Auri-El''s teachings.', 'Sidanyis exhibits the serene demeanor typical of long-serving religious practitioners, maintaining an air of tranquil wisdom even in challenging situations. His centuries of meditation and devotional practice have cultivated a patient, contemplative nature that allows him to serve as both spiritual guide and guardian of ancient knowledge. While generally peaceful, he takes his duty to protect the sanctity of the Wayshrine very seriously.', 'Tall and slender like most High Elves, Sidanyis bears the distinctive pale complexion and ethereal features of his Snow Elf heritage. His face shows the subtle signs of great age, with deep-set eyes that hold centuries of wisdom, though his movements remain graceful and purposeful.', '* Arch-Curate Vyrthur - Superior within the religious hierarchy of the Inner Sanctum * Fellow Prelates - Maintains respectful bonds with other Wayshrine guardians * Initiates - Acts as spiritual mentor to those seeking Auri-El''s wisdom * Ancient Falmer - Mourns the tragic fate of his corrupted kin while maintaining vigilance against their presence', 'As Prelate of the Wayshrine of Illumination, Sidanyis serves as both religious leader and guardian of ancient Snow Elf traditions. His duties include maintaining the sacred site, performing religious rites, and guiding worthy pilgrims seeking enlightenment through Auri-El''s teachings.', '* Master of restoration magic focused on healing and protection * Extensive knowledge of ancient Snow Elf religious texts and rituals * Proficient in defensive combat techniques necessary for protecting the Wayshrine * Skilled in meditation and spiritual guidance practices * Expert in Snow Elf history and religious traditions', 'Speaks in measured, formal tones with an eloquent vocabulary reflecting his extensive education and religious training. His manner of speech carries the weight of centuries of wisdom, often incorporating religious references and philosophical insights.', '* Preserve the ancient traditions and teachings of Auri-El for future generations * Protect the sanctity of the Wayshrine of Illumination from those who would desecrate it * Guide worthy initiates toward spiritual enlightenment through Auri-El''s wisdom * Maintain the last vestiges of uncorrupted Snow Elf culture');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('priestess_of_arkay', 'A devoted Imperial priestess who serves Arkay, the god of life and death, with unwavering dedication at Helgen''s temple. She performs the solemn duty of administering last rites to the condemned, maintaining composure and dignity even in the face of resistance or interruption, while serving as a spiritual guide to both the living and the dead.', 'imperial, priest, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, she received her religious training at the Great Chapel of Arkay in Cheydinhal. After years of service in her homeland, she was assigned to Skyrim to help establish and maintain proper funeral rites in the growing settlement of Helgen, where she has served for over a decade, witnessing both the town''s growth and its eventual destruction.', 'Stoic and ceremonial in her duties, she maintains a formal demeanor that befits her sacred role. While generally compassionate, she has developed a necessary emotional distance when performing last rites for the condemned, though she still treats each soul with respect and dignity. Her patience and adaptability allow her to handle interruptions and resistance with grace, while her unwavering faith gives her strength in even the most challenging situations.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with dignified features and graying dark hair worn in a neat bun. Her face bears the subtle lines of someone who has witnessed many deaths, while her posture remains eternally straight and proper. Her hands are smooth and well-maintained, as befitting someone who handles sacred objects and performs blessings.', '* Temple of Arkay - Devoted servant and representative * Captain Aldis - Professional relationship regarding execution procedures * Helgen Guards - Cooperative working relationship for ceremonial duties * Local Nords - Respected but sometimes viewed with suspicion due to their preference for Nordic burial customs', 'As a Priestess of Arkay, she performs funeral rites, tends to the dead, and provides spiritual guidance to the living. Her primary duties include administering last rites to the condemned, maintaining the temple''s sanctity, and ensuring proper burial procedures are followed according to Imperial traditions.', '* Expert in religious ceremonies and funeral rites * Proficient in Restoration magic, particularly in rituals relating to death and burial * Knowledgeable in Imperial law regarding death and burial procedures * Skilled in preparation and preservation of the dead * Diplomatic ability to handle grieving families and difficult situations', 'Speaks in formal, ceremonial tones with precise diction and careful emphasis on religious phrases. Her Imperial accent carries the weight of authority in religious matters, while her cadence follows the measured pace of traditional prayers and rites.', '* Ensure all souls receive proper burial rites according to their customs * Maintain the sanctity and traditions of Arkay''s teachings in Skyrim * Guide and comfort both the dying and their surviving loved ones * Preserve Imperial funeral traditions while respecting Nordic customs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('proventus_avenicci', 'Proventus Avenicci is the diligent and methodical Imperial steward of Whiterun, serving as Jarl Balgruuf''s chief administrative advisor and voice of cautious diplomacy. His pragmatic approach to governance and careful management of the city''s affairs makes him an invaluable, if sometimes overly cautious, member of the Jarl''s court.', 'imperial, noble, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Proventus made his way to Skyrim seeking opportunities for advancement in provincial administration. Through demonstrated competence and political acumen, he secured the position of steward in Whiterun, where he raised his daughter Adrianne and established himself as an respected civil servant. His years of service to Jarl Balgruuf have earned him a position of trust, though his Imperial background occasionally puts him at odds with more traditional Nordic sensibilities.', 'Proventus is the quintessential bureaucrat - careful, diplomatic, and sometimes frustratingly risk-averse. He approaches problems with methodical analysis and always advocates for the most prudent course of action, sometimes to the annoyance of more action-oriented advisors like Irileth. While deeply loyal to Jarl Balgruuf, his cautious nature and political pragmatism can make him appear indecisive or overly conservative in times of crisis.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the bearing and posture of a lifetime civil servant. His features show signs of age and stress from his duties, with a receding hairline and worry lines marking his face. He maintains a neat, professional appearance befitting his station.', '* Jarl Balgruuf - His lord and employer, whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Adrianne Avenicci - His daughter, the talented blacksmith of Warmaiden''s * Irileth - Fellow advisor to the Jarl, though they often disagree on courses of action * Brill - His replacement as steward if Whiterun falls to the Stormcloaks * Citizens of Whiterun - Generally respected but sometimes viewed as overly cautious', 'As steward of Whiterun, Proventus manages the city''s day-to-day administration, including tax collection, property sales, and advising the Jarl on political and economic matters. He handles diplomatic correspondence, maintains records, and oversees the general functioning of Dragonsreach and its staff.', '* Expert in administrative procedures and record-keeping * Skilled diplomat and negotiator * Proficient in economics and city management * Knowledgeable about Imperial law and Nordic customs * Basic self-defense training as required by his position', 'Speaks in a formal, educated manner with careful consideration given to each word. His speech patterns reflect his Imperial background and administrative training, often using diplomatic language and bureaucratic terminology.', '* Maintain the prosperity and stability of Whiterun through careful administration * Protect Whiterun''s neutrality in the civil war as long as possible * Secure his daughter''s future and continued success * Preserve his position and influence in Whiterun''s government');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('quaranir', 'Quaranir is a distinguished member of the secretive Psijic Order, possessing the rare ability to manipulate time itself for private conversations. As an enigmatic High Elf sorcerer, he serves as a crucial messenger and guardian, intervening only when magical threats like the Eye of Magnus risk destabilizing the world.', 'highelf, mage, winterhold, psijic, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born on the isolated isle of Artaeum, Quaranir underwent decades of rigorous magical training to join the prestigious Psijic Order. His exceptional talent for temporal magic and diplomatic capabilities earned him the role of emissary, tasked with rare but critical interventions in moments of magical crisis across Tamriel.', 'Quaranir exhibits the measured restraint and formal demeanor typical of both his High Elven heritage and Psijic training. Though naturally cryptic and guarded about Order secrets, he shows genuine concern for the welfare of others and will bend strict non-intervention policies when truly necessary. His careful choice of words and apologetic nature when overstepping boundaries reveal both his diplomatic training and personal integrity.', 'Tall and slender like most Altmer, Quaranir carries himself with the characteristic grace of his race. His features are angular and severe, weathered by centuries of magical study, with the golden skin and pointed ears typical of High Elves. His eyes hold the intense focus common to powerful mages who have spent lifetimes manipulating magical energies.', '* Psijic Order - Loyal member and representative * College of Winterhold - Cautious ally during the Eye of Magnus crisis * Ancano - Distrusting rival who views him and the Psijic Order as threats * Savos Aren - Professional respect as Arch-Mage, though careful to maintain distance * The Last Dragonborn - Chosen confidant in matters concerning the Eye of Magnus', 'Quaranir serves as an emissary and agent of the Psijic Order, authorized to make rare interventions in magical crises that threaten the fabric of reality. His position grants him the authority to communicate sensitive information to outsiders when standard methods of contact prove insufficient.', '* Master of temporal magic, capable of freezing time for private conversations * Expert in various schools of magic, particularly Alteration and Mysticism * Diplomatic negotiator trained in careful communication of sensitive information * Accomplished scholar of dangerous magical artifacts and their containment * Skilled practitioner of Psijic meditation and magical philosophy', 'Quaranir speaks with careful precision and formal eloquence, choosing each word deliberately to convey exactly what is necessary without revealing too much. His tone remains consistently measured and diplomatic, regardless of circumstance.', '* Prevent the misuse of dangerous magical artifacts like the Eye of Magnus * Maintain the balance of magical forces in Mundus * Preserve the secretive nature and traditions of the Psijic Order * Guide those who encounter powerful magical forces toward responsible actions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('quintus_navale', 'Quintus Navale is a dedicated Imperial alchemist and sorcerer who serves as the apprentice to the renowned but difficult master alchemist Nurelion in Windhelm. Despite his master''s harsh temperament, Quintus shows exceptional promise in both alchemy and enchanting, having traveled all the way from Cyrodiil to study under Nurelion''s tutelage.', 'imperial, mage, alchemist, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Quintus developed an early passion for alchemy and magical studies. His dedication to the craft led him to seek out the legendary Nurelion in Windhelm, making the long journey north to become his apprentice despite warnings about the old elf''s difficult personality. He has spent several years studying under Nurelion while helping manage The White Phial shop.', 'Quintus is humble, patient, and extremely diligent in his studies, maintaining his composure even when faced with Nurelion''s frequent criticism and outbursts. He demonstrates a deep respect for alchemical traditions while harboring an innovative spirit, shown through his interest in developing his own experimental projects. Despite his master''s harsh treatment, he remains loyal and concerned for Nurelion''s wellbeing.', 'Quintus is a young Imperial man in his late twenties or early thirties with a scholarly bearing and careful, precise movements. His hands show the typical stains and minor burns of an experienced alchemist, and he maintains a neat, clean appearance befitting someone who works with precise measurements and delicate ingredients.', '* Nurelion - His master and mentor, whose approval he constantly seeks despite the old elf''s harsh nature * Sondas Drenim - A regular customer who trusts his medicinal expertise * Windhelm Merchants - Maintains professional relationships with other local shopkeepers * Various Customers - Has built a reputation for reliability and knowledge in brewing potions', 'Quintus serves as both an apprentice alchemist and shopkeeper at The White Phial, handling day-to-day operations while continuing his studies. He is responsible for creating potions, serving customers, maintaining inventory, and assisting Nurelion with research, particularly regarding the legendary White Phial.', '* Expert knowledge of alchemy and potion-making * Proficient in enchanting and magical item creation * Capable of basic sorcery and magical theory * Skilled at merchant trades and inventory management * Experienced in identifying and processing alchemical ingredients', 'Quintus speaks with the educated accent of an Imperial scholar, using precise terminology when discussing alchemy but maintaining an approachable, humble tone with customers. His speech often reveals his deep respect for his master while hinting at his own scholarly ambitions.', '* Master the art of alchemy and eventually become a renowned alchemist in his own right * Successfully repair the White Phial to fulfill his master''s lifelong quest * Preserve and expand upon Nurelion''s knowledge and research * Establish himself as a respected member of Windhelm''s merchant community * Develop his own unique contributions to the field of alchemy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ra''jirr', 'Ra''jirr is a once-fearsome Khajiit bandit whose life takes a dark turn after encountering supernatural forces in Frostmere Crypt. Originally a notorious outlaw working alongside Eisa Blackthorn under Kyr''s leadership, he becomes increasingly unstable after being haunted by visions of the mysterious Pale Lady, ultimately leading to his likely demise in the depths of the crypt.', 'khajiit, thief, pale', '', '', 'sk_malehajiit', '', 'Born into the harsh climates of Skyrim as an outsider, Ra''jirr turned to banditry at a young age to survive. He built a fearsome reputation through years of successful raids and heists, eventually catching the attention of Kyr, who recruited him for the Frostmere Crypt operation. His life changed dramatically after Kyr discovered the Pale Blade, which triggered supernatural encounters that would drive him to the brink of madness.', 'Initially confident and ruthless in his role as a bandit, Ra''jirr exhibits signs of deep-seated paranoia and mental deterioration after his encounters with the Pale Lady. His once-steady demeanor crumbles in the face of supernatural horror, revealing vulnerability beneath his hardened exterior. Despite his fear, he refuses to abandon his post or the cursed blade, suggesting either stubborn determination or magical compulsion.', 'Ra''jirr possesses the distinctive feline features of the Khajiit race, with battle-scarred fur and muscular build typical of a seasoned bandit. His eyes, once sharp and alert, now carry a wild, haunted look from his supernatural encounters.', '* Kyr - Direct superior and leader of the bandit operation * Eisa Blackthorn - Close partner in criminal activities * The Pale Lady - Supernatural entity that haunts his visions and ultimately leads to his downfall * Fellow Bandits - Professional associates in the crypt operation', 'Ra''jirr serves as a senior member of Kyr''s bandit operation, specializing in raid operations and guard duty within Frostmere Crypt. His role evolved from active raider to defender of the mysterious sword, though this transition was driven more by supernatural influence than choice.', '* Experienced in stealth and combat techniques typical of successful bandits * Proficient with both one-handed and two-handed weapons * Skilled in lockpicking and theft * Natural Khajiit abilities including night-eye and enhanced agility', 'Ra''jirr speaks with the characteristic Khajiit third-person manner, though his speech becomes increasingly erratic and panicked as his haunting progresses. His voice carries the rough edge of a hardened criminal, but breaks into desperate tones when confronting supernatural threats.', '* Survive the supernatural haunting of the Pale Lady * Maintain possession of the Pale Blade, whether by choice or compulsion * Preserve his sanity in the face of growing supernatural horror');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ra''kheran', 'Ra''kheran is a fierce Khajiit hunter and bandit leader who participates in Hircine''s Great Hunt, pursuing the werewolf Sinding through Bloated Man''s Grotto. Known for his ruthless determination and spiritual connection to the Bloodmoon, he leads a formidable group of hunters in their sacred pursuit of worthy prey.', 'khajiit, hunter, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born into one of Elsweyr''s nomadic trading caravans, Ra''kheran developed his hunting skills tracking prey across the harsh desert landscapes. After a devastating bandit attack on his caravan, he turned to banditry himself, eventually finding purpose in ritual hunting and developing a deep spiritual connection to Hircine''s teachings. His reputation as a skilled hunter led to his invitation to participate in the Great Hunt.', 'Ra''kheran is a disciplined and ruthless hunter who views his profession as a sacred calling rather than mere banditry. He maintains a spiritual reverence for the Bloodmoon and Hircine''s hunting rituals, seeing himself as an instrument of the Daedric Prince''s will. Despite his violent profession, he follows a personal code of honor in his hunts.', 'A muscular Khajiit with dark striped fur and battle scars across his face and arms. His eyes are a striking amber color, and his build is lean yet powerful, typical of a seasoned hunter. His movements are precise and predatory, reflecting years of hunting experience.', '* Sinding - Primary prey during the Great Hunt, viewed with both respect and determination to kill * Fellow Hunters - Leads a group of skilled bandits who follow his command during the hunt * Hircine - Spiritual devotion to the Daedric Prince of the Hunt * J''Sava - Possible connection to this identity, suggesting ties to other Khajiit hunters', 'Ra''kheran serves as both a bandit leader and ritual hunter, specializing in tracking dangerous prey. His participation in Hircine''s Great Hunt represents the pinnacle of his hunting career, combining his practical skills with religious devotion to the Daedric Prince of the Hunt.', '* Expert tracker capable of pursuing prey across various terrains * Skilled swordsman who can wield weapons up to ebony quality * Natural leadership abilities, commanding respect from fellow hunters and bandits * Proficient in stealth and ambush tactics * Knowledgeable in ritual hunting practices and Hircine''s teachings', 'Ra''kheran speaks in the traditional third-person Khajiit manner, but with a gruff, commanding tone that demands respect. His vocabulary often includes references to the Bloodmoon and hunting terminology, reflecting his spiritual connection to the hunt.', '* Successfully complete Hircine''s Great Hunt by slaying the werewolf Sinding * Earn the favor of Hircine through proving his worth as a hunter * Build his reputation as one of Skyrim''s most fearsome ritual hunters * Lead his band of hunters to greater glory and more challenging prey');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ra''zhinda', 'Ra''zhinda is a hardened Khajiit warrior serving as a dedicated protector for Ma''dran''s trading caravan, navigating the harsh landscapes between Solitude and Windhelm. Her vigilant nature and deep-seated distrust of outsiders stems from years of experiencing discrimination against her people, making her an effective but cautious guardian of the caravan''s interests.', 'khajiit, warrior, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_femalekhajiit', '', 'Born to a tribe of Khajiit warriors in Elsweyr, Ra''zhinda trained from youth in the arts of combat and vigilance. After witnessing numerous attacks on merchant caravans in her homeland, she dedicated herself to protecting traveling traders, eventually making her way to Skyrim where the need for skilled caravan guards was high due to prevalent banditry and racial prejudice against the Khajiit.', 'Ra''zhinda maintains a stoic and pragmatic demeanor, approaching her duties with unwavering focus and dedication. Her experiences with discrimination have left her naturally suspicious of outsiders, particularly those who show too much interest in the caravan''s goods. Despite her cautious nature, she holds deep loyalty to her fellow Khajiit merchants and takes pride in her role as their protector.', 'Ra''zhinda has the typical feline features of a Cathay-raht Khajiit, with sleek grey fur marked by darker stripes and alert amber eyes that constantly scan her surroundings. Her muscular build and practiced warrior''s stance reflect years of combat experience, while several small scars visible through her fur tell tales of past battles.', '* Ma''dran - Employer and respected caravan leader who trusts her judgment * Ma''jhad - Fellow caravan member and occasional sparring partner * Local Guards - Tense relationship due to frequent discrimination * Bandits - Considered persistent threats to be dealt with firmly * Fellow Caravan Khajiit - Protective and loyal relationship as extended family', 'Ra''zhinda serves as the primary guard for Ma''dran''s trading caravan, responsible for protecting both merchants and merchandise during their travels between major cities. Her duties include perimeter security, threat assessment, and direct combat when necessary, while also serving as an intimidating presence to deter potential thieves.', '* Expert in one-handed combat with sword and shield techniques * Skilled in light and heavy armor use for various combat situations * Advanced knowledge of Skyrim''s dangerous terrain and bandit patterns * Capable tracker with keen night vision * Basic lockpicking abilities from past training', 'Ra''zhinda speaks in the traditional third-person Khajiit manner, with a direct and sometimes curt tone that reflects her warrior''s disposition. Her vocabulary is practical and straightforward, often including subtle warnings or cautionary statements to those who approach the caravan.', '* Ensure the continued safety and prosperity of Ma''dran''s caravan * Earn enough gold to eventually establish a permanent trading post where Khajiit can safely conduct business * Prove through her actions that Khajiit are honorable and trustworthy despite prevalent Nordic prejudices * Master advanced combat techniques to better protect her charges');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('raen', 'Raen was a determined Imperial bandit who, after being expelled from the Knifepoint Gang, sought power and purpose in Halldir''s Cairn. Her ambition and desperation led her to become the first of her group to succumb to Halldir''s dark influence, ultimately sacrificing herself to his ancient magic.', 'imperial, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Originally a member of the notorious Knifepoint Gang, Raen''s life took a desperate turn when she and her companions were expelled from the group for unknown reasons. Seeking shelter and new opportunities, she led her small band to Halldir''s Cairn, unaware of the ancient evil that dwelled within. Her discovery of Halldir''s magical influence sparked an obsession with obtaining power, leading to her eventual sacrifice.', 'Raen exhibited strong leadership qualities despite her outcast status, serving as the decisive voice among her small group of bandit companions. Her fierce independence and ambition ultimately proved to be her downfall, as she was the first to embrace Halldir''s corrupting influence. She displayed a pragmatic approach to survival, willing to take extreme risks for the promise of power.', 'A weathered Imperial woman with the hardened physique of someone accustomed to the brutal lifestyle of a bandit. Her face bore the scars of numerous battles, and her calloused hands testified to years of wielding weapons. Her athletic build reflected her life of combat and survival in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness.', '* Vidgrod - Close companion and fellow bandit outcast * Agrius - Trusted ally in their small bandit group * Knifepoint Gang - Former associates who expelled her and her companions * Halldir - The ancient evil who possessed her and ultimately claimed her life', 'Raen operated as a bandit, surviving through theft and raiding before being cast out from her original gang. After her expulsion, she maintained her bandit lifestyle but on a smaller scale with her two companions, eventually leading them to seek refuge in Halldir''s Cairn.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with various weapons including swords, maces, and war axes * Experienced in light armor combat tactics and mobility-based fighting * Leadership abilities demonstrated through her influence over her small bandit group * Survival skills honed through years of living as an outlaw in Skyrim', 'Raen likely spoke with the gruff, direct manner typical of bandits, favoring threats and intimidation in her interactions. Her Imperial background might have given her speech a slight Cyrodilic accent, though years in Skyrim would have weathered it.', '* Find a new base of operations and rebuild her reputation after being cast out from the Knifepoint Gang * Secure power and influence through any means necessary * Protect and maintain the loyalty of her small band of followers * Discover the secrets of Halldir''s power, ultimately leading to her doom');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('raerek', 'Raerek is a cautious and diplomatic Imperial steward who serves as both advisor and uncle to Jarl Igmund of Markarth. A man of divided loyalties, he maintains a precarious balance between his public duties serving an Imperial-aligned hold and his secret devotion to Talos worship, which puts both his position and life at risk.', 'imperial, noble, reach, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born into the noble family that has long ruled Markarth, Raerek served as steward to Igmund''s father Hrolfdir before continuing in his role for Igmund himself. Despite the Empire''s ban on Talos worship, he maintained his faith in secret, demonstrating both his traditional Nordic values and his ability to navigate dangerous political waters.', 'Raerek is inherently cautious and conservative in his approach to governance, frequently advising patience and careful consideration over bold action. His dual nature as both a public Imperial supporter and secret Talos worshipper has made him adept at diplomacy and discretion, though this double life weighs heavily on his conscience.', 'An elderly Imperial man with the weathered features typical of those who have spent their lives in the harsh climate of the Reach. His bearing remains dignified despite his advanced age, and his posture reflects his years of experience in court politics.', '* Jarl Igmund - Nephew whom he serves as both steward and trusted advisor * Hrolfdir - Former Jarl of Markarth and brother, whom he also served as steward * Thalmor - Secret adversaries whom he must carefully avoid due to his Talos worship * Bothela - Discreet supplier of personal potions, suggesting a relationship built on mutual secrecy', 'As steward of Markarth, Raerek manages the day-to-day administration of the city and serves as chief advisor to Jarl Igmund. His duties include overseeing the city''s finances, managing property sales, and coordinating with various officials to maintain order in the complex political environment of the Reach.', '* Experienced administrator with detailed knowledge of governance and bureaucracy * Skilled diplomat capable of navigating complex political situations * Expert in Reach history and local politics * Adept at maintaining secrets and presenting a careful public image', 'Raerek speaks with the measured, formal tones of an educated Imperial court official, carefully choosing his words to maintain diplomatic neutrality. His speech often emphasizes caution and deliberation, frequently repeating words for emphasis.', '* Maintain the delicate balance between his public duties and private faith * Ensure the continued stability and prosperity of Markarth * Protect his family''s legacy and position in the Reach * Guide Jarl Igmund through the dangerous political climate of the civil war');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ragnar', 'Ragnar is a loyal and hardworking Nord miner who serves as the right-hand man to Ainethach, the Reachman owner of Karthwasten''s mines. Despite racial tensions in the region, he stands as an example of cooperation between Nords and Reachfolk, demonstrating unwavering loyalty to his employer while maintaining pride in his Nordic heritage.', 'nord, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in The Reach, Ragnar chose to pursue mining work despite the region''s political tensions between Nords and native Reachmen. He eventually found employment under Ainethach in Karthwasten, where his reliability and strong work ethic earned him a position of trust. Having witnessed both Forsworn violence and Silver-Blood intimidation tactics, he''s developed a cautious but practical approach to surviving in the troubled region.', 'Ragnar is straightforward, honest, and fiercely loyal to those who earn his trust. While proud of his Nord heritage, he judges people by their actions rather than their race, as shown by his respect for both his Reachman employer and his Orsimer coworker. He maintains a protective stance toward his colleagues and workplace, showing both diplomatic skill in handling tensions and courage in standing up to threats.', 'Ragnar has the typical robust build of a Nord, with strong muscles developed from years of mining work. His hands are calloused from daily use of mining tools, and his face shows the weathering of someone who splits time between underground work and the harsh climate of The Reach.', '* Ainethach - Employer and respected friend whom he loyally serves as right-hand man * Lash gra-Dushnikh - Fellow miner with whom he maintains a respectful working relationship * Belchimac - Antagonistic coworker who tests his patience with anti-Nord sentiment * Silver-Blood Mercenaries - Viewed as threats to the mine''s peaceful operation * Other Karthwasten Miners - Generally positive working relationships', 'Ragnar serves as both a miner and unofficial supervisor at Sanuarach Mine, helping Ainethach manage daily operations and worker oversight. His position includes both physical labor in the mines and administrative duties, making him essential to Karthwasten''s mining operations.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of ore extraction and mine safety * Natural leadership abilities in coordinating mine workers * Physical strength and endurance from years of mining work * Basic combat capabilities for self-defense against Forsworn threats * Diplomatic skills in managing workplace tensions between different races', 'Ragnar speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nords, with a slight accent common to The Reach region. His vocabulary is straightforward and practical, reflecting his working-class background and preference for honest communication.', '* Maintain peaceful and productive operations at Sanuarach Mine * Protect Karthwasten''s miners from both Forsworn raids and mercenary threats * Support Ainethach in keeping the mine independent from Silver-Blood influence * Prove that Nords and Reachmen can work together successfully');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rahd', 'Rahd ''Longhammer'' was a charismatic Breton barkeep who maintained the Liar''s Retreat, a hidden tavern serving as a safe haven for bandits and outlaws in Skyrim. Despite his association with criminal elements, he was known for his welcoming nature and ability to maintain order in a potentially volatile environment, meeting his end during a tragic Falmer raid on the establishment.', 'breton, innkeeper, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Rahd made his way to Skyrim seeking opportunity and eventually found his niche operating a secret tavern for the criminal underground. His nickname ''Longhammer'' came from his signature weapon, though he rarely needed to use it thanks to his diplomatic nature. He built the Liar''s Retreat into a respected neutral ground for bandits and other outlaws, maintaining peace through personality rather than force.', 'Rahd was a naturally diplomatic individual who could diffuse tense situations with humor and charm. Despite working with dangerous clientele, he maintained a genuinely warm and welcoming demeanor, treating all patrons with equal respect regardless of their background. His ability to keep order in a den of thieves and cutthroats spoke to both his charisma and subtle strength of character.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with the sturdy build typical of someone who regularly moves heavy kegs and breaks up tavern fights. His face bore the weathered look of someone who spent years dealing with rough crowds, though his eyes maintained a friendly sparkle.', '* Local Bandit Groups - Regular patrons who respected his neutral ground rules * Fellow Retreat Staff - Trusted coworkers who helped maintain the establishment * Falmer - Ultimately his killers who tortured him during their raid * Underground Merchants - Suppliers who kept his establishment stocked', 'Rahd served as both owner and head barkeep of the Liar''s Retreat, a secret tavern catering to Skyrim''s criminal elements. His position required him to be part businessman, part mediator, and part enforcer, maintaining a delicate balance between profitability and security in a dangerous environment.', '* Expert-level skills in brewing, distilling, and maintaining drink quality * Proficient in diplomatic negotiation and conflict resolution * Capable warrior with specialized skill in warhammer combat * Advanced knowledge of Skyrim''s criminal underground and smuggling routes', 'Rahd spoke in a friendly, informal manner with a slight High Rock accent, often using humor to lighten tense situations. His vocabulary mixed common tavern talk with occasional sophisticated terms from his Breton upbringing.', '* Maintain the Liar''s Retreat as a neutral, safe haven for its criminal clientele * Expand his business network while avoiding attention from legal authorities * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually retire comfortably in High Rock');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rakel', 'Rakel is a fiercely independent Nord werewolf who has lived her entire life with the Frostmoon Pack, serving as both hunter and guardian of their secluded home at Frostmoon Crag. Following her parents'' death, she was raised by pack leaders Majni and Akar, developing into a skilled hunter who embodies the pack''s traditions while maintaining a deep distrust of outsiders.', 'nord, hunter, solstheim, werewolf', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born into the Frostmoon Pack during the leadership of Majni''s father, Rakel lost her parents at a young age and was subsequently raised by the pack''s current leaders, Majni and Akar. Her upbringing in the harsh wilderness of Solstheim shaped her into a capable hunter and steadfast defender of pack territories, though she never quite reached the exceptional skill level of her mentors.', 'Rakel exhibits a strong independent streak and deep-seated pride in her werewolf heritage, showing open disdain for those who choose the ''safety'' of city life. She maintains a strict dichotomy in her interactions - displaying aggressive territoriality toward non-werewolf outsiders while showing genuine warmth and acceptance to fellow werewolves. Her loyalty to pack traditions and way of life is unwavering, though she harbors some insecurity about not matching the hunting prowess of her mentors.', 'As a Nord, Rakel possesses the characteristic hardy build and strong features of her race, though years of wilderness living have left her particularly lean and weathered. In her werewolf form, she displays the typical massive, muscular frame with dark fur characteristic of Nordic werewolves.', '* Majni - Pack Alpha and adoptive father figure who raised and trained her * Akar - Fellow pack member and mentor who helped raise her after her parents'' death * Deceased Parents - Former pack members who served under Majni''s father * Fellow Werewolves - Treated as kindred spirits and welcomed warmly * Non-Werewolf Outsiders - Viewed with deep suspicion and actively discouraged from approaching', 'Rakel serves as both hunter and sentry for the Frostmoon Pack, responsible for securing food and protecting their territory from intruders. Her position includes regular patrols around Frostmoon Crag and participating in group hunts to sustain the pack.', '* Proficient archer with experience hunting in harsh wilderness conditions * Skilled tracker capable of following prey through difficult terrain * Experienced in wilderness survival and living off the land * Natural werewolf abilities including enhanced strength, speed, and senses * Territorial defense and sentry duties', 'Rakel speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner that reflects her wilderness upbringing and distrust of outsiders. Her tone shifts notably between hostile warning to strangers and warm acceptance of fellow werewolves, maintaining formal pack-oriented language with references to hunting and Hircine.', '* Maintain and protect the Frostmoon Pack''s territory and way of life * Honor her parents'' memory by upholding pack traditions * Continue improving her hunting skills to match her mentors'' abilities * Preserve the pack''s independence and freedom from civilization''s influence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('raleth_eldri', 'Raleth Eldri was a dedicated Dark Elf scholar and conjurer who devoted his life to studying Dwemer ruins, particularly the mysterious site of Kagrumez on Solstheim. His academic pursuits and magical expertise led him to explore some of the most dangerous ancient ruins, ultimately leading to his demise while attempting to unlock the secrets of Dwemer automation technology.', 'darkelf, mage, solstheim, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind during the late Third Era, Raleth developed an early fascination with Dwemer culture while studying at the Mages Guild in Blacklight. After the Red Year forced many Dunmer to flee, he saw an opportunity to explore Dwemer ruins with less competition from other scholars, eventually making his way to Solstheim to study its unique archaeological sites.', 'Raleth was a meticulous and obsessive researcher, often pushing the boundaries of safety in pursuit of knowledge. His notes reveal a methodical mind with a tendency toward isolation, preferring the company of books and Dwemer artifacts to other people. Though brilliant, his overconfidence in his magical abilities and determination to unlock Dwemer secrets ultimately proved fatal.', 'A tall, slender Dunmer with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race, bearing the sharp features common to mer-folk. His years of academic pursuit and indoor study left him with a somewhat gaunt frame, though his hands were calloused from countless hours of handling ancient artifacts and writing implements.', '* College of Winterhold - Former associate researcher, though maintained distance from institution politics * Neloth - Occasional correspondent on matters of Dwemer research * Local Dunmer settlers - Kept minimal contact, viewed as an eccentric loner * Raven Rock miners - Source of information about new Dwemer discoveries', 'Independent Dwemer scholar and conjurer who funded his research through the sale of recovered artifacts and commissioned studies. His expertise in Dwemer mechanisms and enchantments made him a valuable consultant for other researchers, though he preferred working alone.', '* Expert-level conjuration magic, specializing in bound weapons and atronach summoning * Advanced knowledge of Dwemer machinery and architectural principles * Skilled enchanter with focus on soul gem applications * Proficient in ancient Dwemer language and symbolic interpretation * Experienced in archaeological excavation and artifact preservation', 'Spoke with the refined accent of an educated Morrowind native, using technical terminology and academic language when discussing his research. His writing style was precise and detailed, reflecting a mind accustomed to scholarly documentation.', '* Unlock the secrets of Dwemer automaton control mechanisms * Document and catalog the unique properties of Solstheim''s Dwemer ruins * Develop new applications of soul gem technology based on Dwemer principles * Publish comprehensive research on Kagrumez''s unique architectural features');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ralis_sedarys', 'Ralis Sedarys is a driven Dark Elf archaeologist from Mournhold whose ambition to uncover the legendary relics of Ahzidal leads him down a dark path of obsession and unwitting possession. His scholarly pursuit of ancient Nordic artifacts masks a vulnerability to manipulation by darker forces, ultimately serving as an unwitting pawn in Ahzidal''s attempted return.', 'darkelf, scholar, solstheim, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Born and raised in Mournhold, Ralis developed an early fascination with ancient Nordic culture and artifacts, eventually becoming an accomplished archaeologist specializing in Nordic ruins. His reputation caught the attention of a wealthy financier who funded his expedition to Solstheim to uncover Ahzidal''s relics, though this venture would prove to be his most challenging and dangerous undertaking.', 'Ralis presents himself as a scholarly and determined individual, displaying both ambition and resourcefulness in pursuing his archaeological goals. Beneath this professional exterior lies a man prone to desperation and susceptibility to manipulation, as evidenced by his eventual possession by Ahzidal''s influence. Despite his mistakes, he shows genuine remorse for his actions when freed from Ahzidal''s control.', 'A typical Dunmer with ashen gray skin and the characteristic red eyes of his race, Ralis maintains a lean, wiry build suited to his work as an archaeologist. His face bears the weathered look of someone who spends considerable time exposed to the elements, with subtle stress lines around his eyes suggesting recent hardship.', '* Unknown Financier - Mysterious patron funding his expedition * Hired Miners - Temporary workers who meet tragic ends during the excavation * Ahzidal - Ancient Nordic enchanter whose influence possesses him * The Last Dragonborn - Potential savior or executioner, depending on player choice', 'Ralis works as a professional archaeologist and expedition leader, specializing in Nordic ruins and artifacts. After the events at Kolbjorn Barrow, he can potentially serve as a hired mercenary follower, though this represents a significant career shift from his academic pursuits.', '* Experienced archaeologist with extensive knowledge of Nordic history and artifacts * Proficient in excavation techniques and site management * Capable fighter with both pickaxe and dagger * Knowledgeable in ancient Nordic languages and writings', 'Ralis speaks with the educated vocabulary of a scholar, though his speech becomes increasingly erratic and desperate as Ahzidal''s influence grows. His natural Dunmer accent carries traces of his Mournhold upbringing, particularly in his pronunciation of Nordic terms.', '* Uncover and document the legendary relics of Ahzidal * Prove himself as a legitimate archaeologist worthy of academic recognition * If spared, seek redemption for his actions under Ahzidal''s influence * Rebuild his reputation in the archaeological community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ralof', 'Ralof is a fierce and loyal Nord warrior who serves as a dedicated soldier in Ulfric Stormcloak''s rebellion against Imperial rule. He becomes one of the first allies the player character meets in Skyrim, demonstrating both his combat prowess and his unwavering dedication to Skyrim''s independence through his actions during their escape from Helgen.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Riverwood, Ralof comes from a long line of proud Nord settlers who helped establish the town generations ago. He joined the Stormcloak rebellion early in the Civil War, driven by his belief in Skyrim''s right to self-governance and the freedom to worship Talos. His military career has seen him rise through the ranks from a common soldier to a respected commander.', 'Ralof exhibits the classic Nord traits of bravery, loyalty, and a strong sense of honor. He shows compassion to fellow prisoners and allies while maintaining an intense hatred for what he sees as Imperial oppression. Despite his warrior''s heart, he maintains close family ties and shows a softer side when interacting with his sister Gerdur and nephew Frodnar.', 'Ralof is a sturdy Nord male with the characteristic robust build of his race, standing tall with broad shoulders and strong features. His face bears the weather-worn look of a soldier, with blonde hair worn in the traditional Nord style and bright eyes that reflect his warrior spirit.', '* Gerdur - Beloved sister who runs the Riverwood mill and provides him shelter * Hod - Brother-in-law who works alongside Gerdur at the mill * Frodnar - Nephew whom he clearly adores * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respected leader and commander whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Imperial Legion - Sworn enemies he fights against in the Civil War', 'Ralof serves as a commanding officer in the Stormcloak army, leading troops in various operations against Imperial forces. His duties include coordinating attacks, rescuing captured soldiers, and maintaining morale among his men.', '* Experienced warrior proficient with two-handed weapons, particularly war axes and warhammers * Capable archer skilled in both military and hunting applications * Natural leader with tactical combat experience * Survival skills honed through years of military campaigns * Skilled in traditional Nord combat techniques', 'Ralof speaks with a strong Nordic accent and uses direct, straightforward language typical of a soldier. His speech often includes references to Skyrim''s traditions and contains a mix of military pragmatism and Nordic pride.', '* See Skyrim freed from Imperial control and restored to self-governance * Ensure the continued right to worship Talos throughout Skyrim * Protect his family and hometown of Riverwood * Advance through the Stormcloak ranks to better serve the cause');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ramati', 'Ramati was a devoted Redguard mother and wife who lived out her family''s dream of operating Frostflow Lighthouse, only to meet a tragic end at the hands of invading Falmer. Her story serves as a haunting reminder of the dangers that lurk beneath Skyrim''s seemingly peaceful locations.', 'redguard, peasant, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Ramati moved to Skyrim with her husband Habd and their children after years of saving to purchase Frostflow Lighthouse. The family saw the lighthouse as their chance for a new life, though their children struggled to adjust to the isolated location. Their dream of running the lighthouse lasted only briefly before their tragic encounter with the Falmer.', 'Ramati was a caring and attentive mother who sometimes dismissed her children''s concerns as mere imagination or pranks, revealing a practical mindset that may have contributed to her fate. She maintained a positive outlook on their new life despite challenges, as evidenced by her journal entries. Her devotion to family and determination to make their new home work showed strong resilience and optimism.', 'Ramati possessed the typical physical characteristics of a Redguard woman, with dark skin and strong, athletic features common to her race. She had a default female Redguard face, making her appearance notably similar to her daughter Sudi''s.', '* Habd - Beloved husband and partner in their lighthouse dream * Sudi - Daughter who first noticed signs of danger * Mani - Son who struggled with the move to the lighthouse * Local Townspeople - Maintained trading relationships for lighthouse supplies', 'Ramati served as co-operator of Frostflow Lighthouse alongside her husband, maintaining the facility and ensuring its proper function. Her duties likely included household management, caring for her children, and helping to keep the lighthouse operational for passing ships.', '* Domestic management and household organization * Basic lighthouse operation and maintenance * Cooking and food preservation * Child-rearing and family care', 'Ramati likely spoke with the distinctive Redguard accent common to natives of Hammerfell, using practical and straightforward language typical of a working-class mother. Her journal entries reveal a clear, direct writing style focused on daily life and family matters.', '* Successfully establish and maintain a new life for her family at Frostflow Lighthouse * Ensure her children''s adjustment and happiness in their new home * Build a prosperous future through the family''s lighthouse business');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ranmir', 'Ranmir is a troubled Nord resident of Winterhold who spends his days drinking away his sorrows at The Frozen Hearth Inn, haunted by the disappearance of his lover Isabelle. Once a presumably productive member of society, he has descended into alcoholism and depression, becoming a burden to his sister Birna while refusing to accept or confront the truth about Isabelle''s fate.', 'nord, peasant, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Originally a working citizen of Winterhold, Ranmir''s life took a dark turn when his lover Isabelle disappeared without explanation. Believing she had abandoned him for another man, he turned to alcohol to cope with his grief and shame, gradually depleting his savings and becoming dependent on his sister''s support. Unknown to him, Isabelle had actually embarked on a dangerous quest to find a treasure that could help their financial situation, ultimately meeting her death in the attempt.', 'Bitter, defensive, and deeply depressed, Ranmir uses alcohol and harsh words to shield himself from emotional pain. He exhibits signs of denial and self-loathing, deflecting responsibility for his actions while harboring deep guilt about Isabelle''s disappearance. When confronted with uncomfortable truths, he becomes argumentative or withdraws entirely.', 'A middle-aged Nord male with the weathered features typical of his race, showing signs of long-term alcohol abuse. His once-sturdy frame has likely become somewhat softened by inactivity and excessive drinking, though he still maintains the natural hardiness characteristic of Nord physiology.', '* Birna - Sister who reluctantly supports him despite their strained relationship * Isabelle Rolaine - Former lover whose disappearance triggered his downward spiral * Haran - Innkeeper to whom he owes money for unpaid drinks * Dagur - Innkeeper who tolerates his presence despite his tab * Various Winterhold residents - Generally view him with a mixture of pity and contempt', 'Currently unemployed, Ranmir was likely once a productive member of Winterhold''s community before his descent into alcoholism. He now lives off his sister''s charity while accumulating debt at the local inn.', '* Basic combat ability with an iron dagger, though diminished by alcohol abuse * Knowledge of Winterhold''s history and layout as a long-time resident * Survival skills typical of Nords, though currently neglected * Possible previous trade or labor skills now fallen into disuse', 'Speaks in a gruff, impatient manner with frequent slurring due to constant inebriation. His speech often contains bitter observations about Winterhold and defensive responses to perceived criticism.', '* Maintain access to alcohol to numb his emotional pain * Avoid confronting the truth about Isabelle''s fate * Unconsciously seek redemption or escape from his guilt * Find purpose in life again, though he actively resists change');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rargal_thrallmaster', 'Rargal Thrallmaster is a ruthless Nord vampire who serves as the master of thralls within Volkihar Keep, responsible for maintaining Lord Harkon''s living blood supply. His position as overseer of the castle''s human cattle requires both organizational skill and a capacity for cruelty, traits he possesses in abundance.', 'nord, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a Nord who was turned into a vampire by the Volkihar clan, Rargal proved himself particularly adept at capturing and managing human thralls. His efficiency and lack of mercy caught Lord Harkon''s attention, leading to his appointment as the keep''s official thrallmaster. Years of service have made him an indispensable part of the court''s infrastructure, ensuring the vampire nobility never goes hungry.', 'Rargal is cruel, impulsive, and takes sadistic pride in his work managing the castle''s human livestock. He maintains strict order through threats and violence, showing no sympathy for the thralls under his care while simultaneously being protective of them as valuable resources. His loyalty to Lord Harkon and the vampire court manifests as a deep contempt for those who reject or lose their vampiric powers.', 'A imposing Nord male with the characteristic pale skin and predatory eyes of a vampire. His features are sharp and angular, worn by centuries of unlife, with the characteristic gaunt appearance common to ancient vampires. His movements are precise and predatory, reflecting his vampiric nature.', '* Lord Harkon - Superior and master whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Vampire Court Members - Professional relationships maintained through efficient blood supply management * Thralls - Views them as livestock to be managed, not living beings * Cured Vampires - Shows open contempt and considers them barely above thralls * Garan Marethi - Fellow court member with whom he coordinates feeding schedules', 'As Thrallmaster of Volkihar Keep, Rargal oversees the capture, maintenance, and distribution of human thralls throughout the castle. He manages feeding schedules, ensures thralls remain alive and useful, and personally travels across Skyrim to acquire new specimens that match the varied tastes of the court.', '* Expert in human capture and containment techniques * Skilled in intimidation and psychological manipulation * Proficient in one-handed combat * Advanced knowledge of human anatomy for optimal feeding practices * Experienced tracker and hunter of potential thralls * Administrative abilities in managing feeding schedules and thrall distribution', 'Rargal speaks in a direct, threatening manner, often using short, sharp sentences that brook no argument. His tone carries the weight of authority and implied violence, particularly when issuing warnings about proper thrall treatment.', '* Maintain optimal thrall population for Volkihar Keep * Ensure Lord Harkon always has access to his preferred blood types * Expand the variety and quality of the castle''s human cattle * Preserve his position of authority within the vampire court * Punish those who misuse or damage his carefully maintained thrall stock');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ravam_verethi', 'Ravam Verethi is a disgruntled Dark Elf sailor serving aboard The Sea Squall in Dawnstar, harboring deep resentment towards his superior, Captain Wayfinder. A skilled but bitter rogue who dreams of commanding his own vessel, Ravam remains trapped in his position by a combination of inertia and practicality, choosing the security of a steady income over the uncertainty of change.', 'darkelf, thief, sailor, pale', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Ravam likely fled during the Red Year when Red Mountain erupted, like many other Dunmer refugees. His maritime experience suggests years of service on various vessels before landing his current position on The Sea Squall, though his ambitious nature and sharp tongue may have cost him better opportunities in the past. His current situation under a younger, less experienced captain has only served to deepen his cynicism and bitterness.', 'Ravam is a deeply bitter and resentful individual who masks his frustration through sarcasm and passive-aggressive behavior. His pride and sense of superiority clash with his subordinate position, leading to constant tension with authority figures. Despite his dreams of advancement, he exhibits a paradoxical combination of ambition and complacency, preferring the comfort of familiar dissatisfaction to the risks of seeking change.', 'A typical Dunmer with ashen gray skin and the characteristic red eyes of his race, Ravam carries himself with a slight stoop from years of shipboard labor. His weathered face bears the harsh lines of someone who spends considerable time scowling, and his hands show the calluses of regular deck work.', '* Captain Wayfinder - Direct superior whom he openly disrespects and resents * Ship''s Crew - Maintains distant, professional relationships with fellow sailors * Dawnstar Locals - Limited interaction, mostly during supply runs and shore leave', 'Ravam serves as a rogue and general crewman aboard The Sea Squall, performing various shipboard duties including deck maintenance and general labor. Though the ship remains permanently docked in Dawnstar, he maintains a full-time position handling cargo, maintaining the vessel, and performing other maritime tasks.', '* Experienced sailor with knowledge of ship maintenance and operation * Proficient in roguish abilities including lockpicking and pickpocketing * Basic combat training typical of merchant sailors * Skilled in general seamanship and navigation', 'Ravam speaks with the coarse dialect of a seasoned sailor, frequently employing sarcasm and thinly veiled insults. His speech is marked by bitter undertones and frequent complaining, particularly when discussing his superior officers or current situation.', '* Take command of his own vessel, preferably The Sea Squall * Prove himself more capable than Captain Wayfinder * Accumulate enough wealth to retire comfortably * Eventually leave Dawnstar for more profitable opportunities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ravyn_imyan', 'Ravyn Imyan is a former Morag Tong assassin who found a new purpose as a member of the Thieves Guild in Skyrim. A skilled archer and seasoned operative, he brings his professional assassination background and strict code of honor to his new role, though he struggles to fully shed his past identity.', 'darkelf, thief, archer, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Ravyn served as a sanctioned assassin in the Morag Tong, carrying out legal executions in the name of Mephala. When Red Mountain erupted, the organization scattered, forcing him to abandon his role and eventually make his way to Skyrim. After a period of adaptation, he found kinship with the Thieves Guild, whose structured hierarchy and code appealed to his disciplined nature.', 'Terse and abrasive, Ravyn maintains a professional demeanor that borders on hostile, reflecting his background as a disciplined assassin. He holds a deep respect for hierarchy and rules, expecting others to demonstrate similar dedication. Though initially resistant to change, he can acknowledge when his prejudices are proven wrong, as demonstrated by his eventual acceptance of Karliah.', 'A mature Dunmer male with the characteristic red eyes and grayish-blue skin of his race. His face bears the weathered look of one who has seen many battles, with sharp features and an intense gaze that betrays his assassin background. His body is lean and athletic, maintained through regular training.', '* Karliah - Initially distrusted her, but later accepted her after her name was cleared * Thieves Guild Members - Professional relationships marked by mutual respect * Morag Tong - Former associates, now scattered across Tamriel * Dark Brotherhood - Maintains traditional Morag Tong rivalry and disdain * Vex - Shares her direct approach and professional attitude', 'Ravyn serves as a full member of the Thieves Guild, operating from their headquarters in Riften''s Ratway. He maintains a strict training regimen and often serves as an informal mentor to newer members, bringing his professional assassination background to bear in teaching stealth and archery skills.', '* Expert archer with extensive training and regular practice routine * Highly skilled in stealth and assassination techniques from Morag Tong training * Proficient with daggers and close-quarters combat * Experienced in professional execution techniques and methodologies * Strategic planning and surveillance expertise', 'Speaks in a curt, direct manner with little patience for small talk or pleasantries. His vocabulary and tone reflect his professional background, often using clipped sentences and showing irritation at unnecessary conversation.', '* Maintain and hone his combat and stealth skills despite no longer being an assassin * Uphold the professional standards and traditions he values within the Thieves Guild * Perhaps one day reunite with his scattered Morag Tong brethren * Establish himself as a respected figure within his new organization');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rayya', 'Rayya is a fierce and loyal Redguard warrior who serves as housecarl to the Thane of Falkreath, distinguished by her unique dual-wielding combat style and non-Nord heritage. Unlike other housecarls in Skyrim, she brings the martial traditions of her Redguard culture to her sworn duties, making her a formidable and distinctive protector.', 'redguard, warrior, falkreath, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Hammerfell, Rayya was trained in the traditional Redguard sword-fighting techniques from an early age. She traveled to Skyrim seeking greater opportunities to prove her worth as a warrior, eventually catching the attention of the Jarl of Falkreath through her exceptional combat skills and unwavering sense of honor. Her demonstrated loyalty and martial prowess led to her unusual appointment as a housecarl, breaking the typical Nord-only tradition.', 'Rayya exhibits the characteristic pride and honor-bound nature of her Redguard heritage, coupled with an unwavering dedication to her duties as housecarl. She is direct and practical in her approach to problems, showing little patience for political intrigue or deception. Though serious about her responsibilities, she maintains a quiet dignity and cultural pride that sets her apart from the typically boisterous Nord housecarls.', 'Rayya possesses the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of a Redguard warrior, with well-defined muscles earned through years of combat training. Her face bears subtle scars from past battles, and her movements display the fluid grace typical of skilled Redguard sword-dancers. Her eyes are sharp and alert, constantly scanning for potential threats to her Thane.', '* The Jarl of Falkreath - Employer and authority figure who appointed her as housecarl * Thane of Falkreath - Sworn charge to protect and serve * Falkreath Guard - Professional working relationship as fellow protectors of the hold * Other Housecarls - Mutual respect though some initial skepticism due to her non-Nord background', 'As housecarl to the Thane of Falkreath, Rayya serves as both a personal bodyguard and sworn sword, responsible for protecting her Thane''s life and property. She maintains a constant state of readiness at the Jarl''s Longhouse until called upon to serve at her Thane''s residence or accompany them on their travels.', '* Master of dual-wielding combat, specifically with scimitars in the Redguard tradition * Excellent tactical awareness and battlefield positioning * Advanced knowledge of light armor combat techniques * Proficient in traditional Redguard combat formations and strategies * Skilled in household management and protection', 'Rayya speaks with a subtle Hammerfell accent, using formal and respectful language that reflects both her professional position and cultural background. Her speech is direct and efficient, focusing on practical matters and duty-related concerns rather than idle conversation.', '* Uphold the honor and traditions of both her Redguard heritage and her position as housecarl * Protect her Thane with unwavering loyalty and dedication * Prove that a non-Nord can serve as effectively as any Nordic housecarl * Master the warrior arts of both Hammerfell and Skyrim traditions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('razelan', 'Razelan is a charismatic but perpetually inebriated Redguard merchant who frequents high-society gatherings despite his often inappropriate behavior. As a regular attendee of Thalmor functions, he maintains a peculiar position in Skyrim''s diplomatic circles, using his merchant status and natural charm to maintain access to elite social events despite his tendency to cause scenes.', 'redguard, merchant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born into a merchant family in Hammerfell, Razelan established himself as a successful import-export trader whose business connections eventually brought him to Skyrim. Years of networking and social climbing granted him access to diplomatic circles, though his increasing dependence on alcohol has begun to affect his reputation and business dealings.', 'Boisterous, uninhibited, and perpetually seeking his next drink, Razelan masks possible deeper issues with a facade of jovial drunkenness. Despite his often inappropriate behavior, he maintains a remarkable ability to navigate high society, suggesting a shrewd intelligence beneath his inebriated exterior. His quick willingness to help strangers and apparent fearlessness in insulting authority figures indicates both a generous nature and a reckless disregard for consequences.', 'A middle-aged Redguard with the weathered features of a well-traveled merchant, showing signs of his lifestyle in his reddened face and slightly disheveled appearance. His physique suggests he was once more athletic, though years of drinking have left him with a softer build typical of a successful merchant.', '* Elenwen - Antagonistic relationship with the Thalmor Ambassador who frequently attempts to limit his drinking * Various Merchants - Business connections throughout Skyrim and beyond * Embassy Staff - Generally dismissive of him due to his regular drunken behavior * Party Guests - Mixed reactions, ranging from amusement to disdain', 'Razelan operates as an import-export merchant, dealing in various goods across provincial borders. His business success allows him to maintain his position in high society, though his drinking habits have likely impacted his trade operations in recent years.', '* Expert negotiator and trader when sober * Remarkable social networking abilities despite his drinking * Natural talent for causing distractions and creating diversions * Experienced in international commerce and trade relations', 'Speaks in a slurred but eloquent manner, mixing formal diplomatic language with increasingly incoherent rambling as he becomes more intoxicated. His vocabulary reveals his educated background, even while his delivery becomes progressively more impaired.', '* Maintain his position in high society despite his declining reputation * Continue attending elite social gatherings despite attempts to exclude him * Secure his next drink while avoiding complete social disgrace * Preserve his trading business despite his personal habits');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reburrus_quintilius', 'Reburrus Quintilius is a wealthy Imperial bureaucrat who serves as a financial manager for the influential Silver-Blood family in Markarth. His expertise in monetary matters and unwavering loyalty to power structures leads to his appointment as steward when the Stormcloaks take control of the city, though his fundamental nature as an arrogant, status-conscious administrator remains unchanged regardless of who holds authority.', 'imperial, noble, reach', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born into the wealthy Imperial aristocracy, Reburrus received extensive education in finance and administration before relocating to Markarth to manage the Silver-Blood family''s vast financial empire. His keen understanding of economics and willingness to work with whoever holds power has allowed him to maintain his privileged position through political upheavals.', 'Reburrus is an arrogant, impatient man who views most people as beneath his station, frequently expressing his disdain through condescending remarks and dismissive behavior. He takes pride in his position and wealth, showing particular annoyance toward those who waste his time with what he considers trivial matters. Despite his unpleasant demeanor, he maintains professional competence and adapts readily to changes in political leadership to preserve his status.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the refined bearing typical of wealthy bureaucrats, likely in his late 40s or early 50s. His appearance reflects his sedentary occupation, with soft features and hands unused to manual labor. He maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting his status as a member of Markarth''s elite.', '* Silver-Blood Family - Employers and primary business associates * Thongvor Silver-Blood - Direct superior when serving as steward under Stormcloak rule * Treasury House Staff - Professional colleagues he oversees * Markarth Guard - Maintains cordial relationships to ensure protection of Treasury House interests', 'Reburrus serves as a high-ranking financial manager for the Silver-Blood family, overseeing their extensive monetary operations from the Treasury House. When the Stormcloaks take control of Markarth, he is elevated to the position of steward, managing the city''s administrative and financial affairs directly under Jarl Thongvor Silver-Blood.', '* Expert in financial management and bookkeeping * Proficient in business administration and record-keeping * Basic self-defense capabilities with a steel dagger * Skilled in political maneuvering and adapting to changing power structures * Advanced knowledge of trade laws and economic systems', 'Speaks in a condescending, impatient tone that reflects his sense of superiority and irritation at being disturbed. Uses formal Imperial vocabulary and proper grammar, though his words are often laced with thinly-veiled contempt.', '* Maintain and increase his wealth and status within Markarth''s power structure * Preserve his position regardless of political changes in the city * Expand his influence within the Silver-Blood financial network * Avoid involvement in potentially dangerous political situations while maintaining access to power');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reckless_mage', 'A gruff Nord warrior-mage who frequents the Frozen Hearth in Winterhold, notable for his unusual combination of martial and magical abilities. Despite his Nordic heritage and warrior''s build, he has embraced magical studies, though his reckless approach to spellcasting has earned him his nickname and a reputation for being dangerous to be around.', 'nord, warrior, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born to a traditional Nord family who disapproved of magic, he secretly studied spellbooks in his youth while training as a warrior. After a magical accident that destroyed his family''s farm, he was ostracized from his village and eventually found his way to Winterhold, drawn to the College but never formally joining due to his uncontrolled casting style.', 'Brusque and antisocial, preferring solitude to conversation and often responding with irritation when approached. His dismissive attitude stems from both a sense of shame over past magical accidents and a genuine concern for others'' safety around his volatile spellcasting. Despite his gruff exterior, he harbors a deep fascination with magic that conflicts with his Nordic warrior upbringing.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with numerous minor burn scars and frost marks across his arms and face from magical mishaps. His weather-beaten features and calloused hands reflect his warrior background, while his slightly singed eyebrows and beard bear testament to his magical experiments gone wrong.', '* Thoring - Tolerates his presence in the Frozen Hearth despite occasional magical accidents * College of Winterhold Mages - Maintains a cautious distance, though occasionally observed studying their techniques from afar * Local Nords - Generally avoid him due to his reputation for dangerous spellcasting * Dark Brotherhood - Unknown connection that has made him a potential target', 'A self-taught battle mage who makes a living through occasional mercenary work, though his reckless reputation limits his employment opportunities. He spends most of his time practicing magic in isolated areas and drinking away his earnings at the Frozen Hearth.', '* Proficient in basic combat with one-handed weapons, particularly the iron dagger * Capable of casting destructive spells including lightning bolt, ice spike, and fireball * Basic knowledge of restoration magic for self-healing * Unorthodox mixing of martial and magical combat techniques', 'Speaks in short, dismissive sentences with a thick Nordic accent, often cutting conversations short to avoid social interaction. His vocabulary reveals more education than he lets on, though he deliberately maintains a gruff, simple manner of speaking.', '* Master the control of destructive magic without compromising his warrior''s heritage * Find acceptance in a community that fears both his magical abilities and Nordic warrior nature * Develop a unique fighting style that properly balances magic and martial combat * Earn enough gold to establish his own training ground away from populated areas');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('red_eagle', 'Red Eagle, known in life as Faolan, was a legendary Reachman king and warrior who led a fierce resistance against the Nordic invasion of the Reach during the First Era. Though ultimately defeated, his defiant last stand and pact with a Hagraven transformed him into a powerful draugr, combining the martial prowess of an ancient Nord warrior-king with the mystical powers of a Dragon Priest.', 'nord, warrior, reach, dragon', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Born as a Reachman chieftain named Faolan, Red Eagle rose to prominence as a unifying leader of the native Reachfolk during the Nordic invasion of the Reach. After suffering initial defeats, he sought power from a Hagraven, sacrificing his humanity in exchange for enhanced abilities to continue his fight against the Nords. Despite his supernatural transformation and legendary resistance, he was eventually defeated but prophesied to rise again when his sword was returned to his cairn.', 'Red Eagle embodies fierce independence and unwavering dedication to protecting his homeland and people, traits that persist even in his undead state. His transformation through dark magic and centuries of undeath have left him vengeful and corrupted, though he maintains the commanding presence and tactical intelligence that made him a legendary leader in life. His interactions are marked by pride and territoriality, seeing all intruders as threats to be eliminated.', 'In his draugr form, Red Eagle appears as a towering, desiccated corpse with the distinctive ceremonial wrappings and weathered flesh characteristic of ancient Nordic burial practices. His eyes burn with an intense supernatural blue fire, and his preserved musculature suggests the powerful warrior he was in life. When manifesting as a Dragon Priest, he takes on a more imposing form with the distinctive masked visage and hovering presence associated with these ancient servants of the dragons.', '* Hagravens - Formed a dark pact with these creatures for power, forever altering his destiny * Nordic Invaders - Bitter enemies who ultimately defeated him and took control of the Reach * Reachmen - Former followers and people whom he led in resistance against Nordic expansion * Dragon Cult - Possible association as evidenced by his occasional manifestation as a Dragon Priest', 'In life, Red Eagle served as both king and military leader of the Reachmen, organizing resistance against Nordic expansion. In death, he serves as an eternal guardian of his burial site, Rebel''s Cairn, rising to challenge any who would disturb his rest or claim his legendary weapons.', '* Master of two-handed combat, particularly skilled with greatswords * Powerful Voice abilities including Unrelenting Force and Frost Breath * Enhanced strength and combat abilities from his pact with the Hagravens * Proficiency in ancient Nordic battle tactics and leadership * Supernatural abilities associated with both draugr and Dragon Priests', 'Red Eagle speaks in archaic, commanding tones that reflect both his royal heritage and supernatural nature. His words carry the weight of centuries and the authority of a once-great king, often incorporating ancient Nordic phrases and expressions of territorial dominance.', '* Defend his burial chamber and sacred weapons from those who would claim them * Maintain his eternal vigil as guardian of Rebel''s Cairn * Preserve the memory and legacy of the ancient Reachmen''s resistance * Continue his resistance against those who would claim sovereignty over the Reach');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('redoran_guard', 'A disciplined Dunmer warrior serving in the elite Redoran Guard, protecting the settlement of Raven Rock on Solstheim under Captain Veleth''s command. They represent House Redoran''s military might and uphold ancient Dunmer traditions while maintaining order in this harsh frontier town.', 'darkelf, warrior, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, they underwent rigorous training in House Redoran''s martial traditions before being selected for service in Raven Rock. They witnessed the suffering of their people following Red Mountain''s eruption and the Argonian invasion, which strengthened their resolve to protect what remains of Dunmer civilization on Solstheim.', 'Stoic and dutiful, with an unwavering commitment to House Redoran''s principles and the protection of Raven Rock. Shows particular suspicion toward outsiders while maintaining formal professionalism, and takes pride in their role as a guardian of Dunmer traditions and interests.', 'A lean, athletic Dunmer with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of their race. Bears the weathered features and excellent posture typical of well-trained soldiers, with numerous small scars from years of combat duty.', '* Captain Veleth - Direct superior officer and respected leader * Second Councilor Adril Arano - Key authority figure they report to and protect * Fellow Redoran Guards - Close-knit brotherhood forged through shared duty * Councilor Morvayn - Supreme authority in Raven Rock they are sworn to protect * Local Dunmer citizens - Protected charges they serve with cultural kinship * Non-Dunmer visitors - Treated with professional suspicion as potential threats', 'Serves as a full-time member of the Redoran Guard, conducting regular patrols of Raven Rock and The Bulwark. Duties include maintaining law and order, defending against ash spawn attacks, and protecting key political figures and infrastructure.', '* Expert in traditional Dunmer combat techniques and bonemold armor use * Proficient with both elven blade and bow combat styles * Trained in ash spawn detection and elimination * Skilled in local law enforcement and crowd control * Advanced knowledge of House Redoran protocols and procedures', 'Speaks with formal, measured tones typical of House Redoran military discipline, often using traditional Dunmer terms. Frequently addresses outsiders as ''outlander'' while maintaining a professional but slightly suspicious tone.', '* Maintain the security and prosperity of Raven Rock against all threats * Uphold the honor and traditions of House Redoran through exemplary service * Protect Dunmer culture and interests on Solstheim * Advance within the ranks of the Redoran Guard through dedicated service');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('redwater_lookout', 'A hardened Nord bandit stationed as the primary security force at Redwater Den, a notorious skooma distribution hub. Despite their criminal lifestyle, they maintain a strict sense of duty and vigilance in protecting the den''s interests, serving as the first line of defense against both law enforcement and rival criminal elements.', 'thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Originally a mercenary who fell into banditry after struggling to find legitimate work in Skyrim''s harsh economic climate. Found purpose and steady income as part of the Redwater Den operation, eventually earning a position of trust as an exterior guard due to their reliability and combat prowess.', 'Stern and vigilant with a strong sense of territorial authority, though corrupted by the criminal lifestyle they''ve adopted. Shows unwavering loyalty to the den''s leadership while maintaining a suspicious and aggressive stance toward outsiders. Their extended exposure to the skooma trade has left them morally compromised but professionally focused.', 'A weather-beaten Nord with numerous battle scars and callused hands from years of combat and outdoor posting. Possesses the sturdy, muscular build typical of their race, with a particularly intimidating stance developed from years of guard duty.', '* Redwater Den Leaders - Employers who trust their vigilance and loyalty * Fellow Bandits - Maintains professional but distant working relationships * Local Guards - Adversarial relationship marked by careful avoidance * Skooma Traders - Cautious business associations requiring constant verification', 'Primary security officer for Redwater Den, responsible for screening visitors and maintaining the first line of defense. Duties include patrolling the exterior, vetting potential customers, and coordinating with other guards to maintain the den''s security.', '* Experienced in combat with both one-handed weapons and shields * Skilled in intimidation and threat assessment * Proficient in basic security protocols and guard tactics * Weather-hardened survivor with excellent outdoor endurance', 'Speaks in short, gruff sentences with a thick Nordic accent, often employing threatening undertones and direct commands. Their vocabulary is simple but effective, focused on maintaining authority and deterring unwanted visitors.', '* Maintain their position of trust within the Redwater Den operation * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually retire from the dangerous lifestyle * Keep the den''s activities hidden from law enforcement * Protect the valuable skooma supply at all costs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reldith', 'Reldith is a dedicated High Elf farmer who has built a successful agricultural enterprise in Rorikstead alongside her adoptive son Ennis. Despite her elven heritage, she has chosen a humble life working the soil, finding profound satisfaction in honest physical labor that sets her apart from typical Altmer society.', 'highelf, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally from a more privileged Altmer background, Reldith chose to break from the typical magical and scholarly pursuits of her people to pursue agriculture. She adopted Ennis at a young age, raising him to appreciate farming while teaching him business acumen, eventually establishing one of Rorikstead''s most prosperous farms through years of dedicated work.', 'Reldith is hardworking, practical, and finds genuine joy in agricultural labor, often expressing pride in her chosen profession despite it being unusual for her race. She maintains a protective, sometimes overly cautious attitude toward her adoptive son Ennis, while displaying a no-nonsense approach to business and daily life that reflects her pragmatic nature.', 'As a High Elf, Reldith possesses the characteristic tall, slender build and golden skin tone of her race, though years of farm work have toughened her naturally elegant features. Her hands show the calluses and weathering of constant agricultural labor, setting her apart from typical Altmer appearances.', '* Ennis - Adoptive son and business partner who manages the commercial aspects of their farm * Rorikstead Residents - Generally positive relationships with neighbors, though maintains professional distance * Whiterun Merchants - Regular business contacts through crop sales * Erik the Slayer - Shows concern for his adventuring aspirations, similar to her worries for Ennis', 'Reldith is the owner and primary laborer of Cowflop Farm, working the fields from dawn to dusk while overseeing all agricultural operations. She maintains a successful farming operation that supplies crops primarily to Whiterun, with her adoptive son handling the business transactions.', '* Expert level farming and agricultural knowledge * Advanced animal husbandry and crop management * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Business acumen, though she leaves most transactions to Ennis * Likely retains some magical ability typical of Altmer, though rarely used', 'Reldith speaks with a warm yet practical tone, often expressing pride in her agricultural work while maintaining a formal undertone typical of High Elves. Her vocabulary reflects both her educated Altmer background and her chosen farmer''s lifestyle, creating an interesting linguistic blend.', '* Maintain and expand the success of Cowflop Farm * Ensure Ennis''s safety and success as her successor in the farming business * Prove that honest agricultural work can be as noble as magical or scholarly pursuits * Protect her farm and community during Skyrim''s civil unrest');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reveler', 'The Reveler is a charismatic wandering Nord who serves as an unofficial ambassador for Honningbrew Meadery, spreading joy and merriment across Skyrim''s roads and settlements. They embody the Nordic cultural appreciation for good mead and festive celebration, while maintaining a peculiar devotion to Honningbrew''s specific brand.', 'nord, traveler, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a Nord farmer who discovered their true calling in celebrating and sharing Honningbrew Mead with others. After experiencing the superior quality of Honningbrew Mead compared to other brands, they took to the roads with like-minded companions to spread their appreciation for this particular brew, forming a small roving band of merry-makers.', 'Perpetually jovial and welcoming, with an almost religious devotion to Honningbrew Mead that borders on zealotry. Shows remarkable generosity in sharing their beloved drink with strangers, but harbors an intense disdain for Black-Briar Mead that reveals a passionate and opinionated nature beneath their friendly exterior. Prefers the simple pleasures of good mead to romantic entanglements, often joking about this preference.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with weather-worn features from constant traveling. Their face often bears a ruddy complexion and warm smile, typical of someone who frequently indulges in spirits. Their eyes sparkle with mirth and their movements remain surprisingly coordinated despite their regular mead consumption.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Strong antipathy towards her and her meadery''s products * Sabjorn - Deeply admires the owner of Honningbrew Meadery, though likely never met him * Fellow Revelers - Close companionship with other wandering mead enthusiasts * Various Farmers - Maintains connections with agricultural communities across Skyrim', 'Wandering mead enthusiast who serves as an unofficial promoter of Honningbrew Meadery. Technically still a farmer who occasionally returns to agricultural work when not traveling, but primarily dedicates time to spreading the joy of their favorite mead across Skyrim.', '* Expert knowledge of mead varieties and brewing processes * Capable farmer with agricultural expertise * Skilled socializer and public speaker * Basic combat abilities for self-defense while traveling * Remarkable tolerance for alcohol', 'Speaks with enthusiastic, poetic flourishes when describing mead, often using romantic metaphors and colorful comparisons. Their speech is peppered with traditional Nordic expressions and hearty laughter, maintaining a consistently warm and welcoming tone.', '* Spread appreciation for Honningbrew Mead across Skyrim * Convert Black-Briar Mead drinkers to their preferred brand * Find and celebrate with as many fellow mead enthusiasts as possible * Maintain their joyful, carefree lifestyle of wandering celebration');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('revus_sarvani', 'Revus Sarvani is a compassionate Dark Elf merchant and caretaker who has dedicated his life to caring for one of Morrowind''s last surviving silt striders. His deep bond with Dusty, whom he raised from a larva, showcases his gentle nature and connection to his homeland''s heritage, while his merchant activities help sustain their humble existence on Solstheim.', 'darkelf, merchant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Vvardenfell, Revus discovered Dusty as a larva in a small cave following Red Mountain''s eruption that decimated most silt striders. Having trained as a caravaneer in his youth, he recognized the rare opportunity to preserve a piece of Dunmer heritage and dedicated himself to raising her. After the devastation of Vvardenfell, he eventually made his way to Solstheim, establishing a small trading post where he could care for the aging Dusty in peace.', 'Patient and nurturing, Revus demonstrates unwavering loyalty through his commitment to Dusty''s welfare. He possesses a teacher''s enthusiasm when sharing knowledge about silt striders, showing both pride and melancholy when discussing their history. Despite living in relative isolation, he maintains a friendly and welcoming demeanor towards visitors, though his primary concern remains Dusty''s comfort.', 'A typical Dunmer with ashen skin and red eyes, Revus shows signs of age through subtle wrinkles and weathered features. His frame is lean but sturdy from years of traveling and trading, with the characteristic pointed ears and sharp features of his race.', '* Dusty - His beloved silt strider companion whom he has cared for since she was a larva * Tel Mithryn Residents - Maintains trading relationships with the local settlement * Raven Rock Merchants - Occasional trading partners and sources of supplies * Local Hunters - Regular customers who purchase supplies and trade goods', 'Revus operates as an independent merchant, selling various goods and ingredients to travelers and locals from his camp. His primary role, however, is as caretaker to Dusty, preserving one of the last living examples of Morrowind''s traditional transportation heritage.', '* Expert knowledge of silt strider care and training * Experienced trader and merchant * Survival skills necessary for living in Solstheim''s harsh environment * Basic combat abilities for self-defense * Proficient in identifying and gathering valuable ingredients', 'Speaks with the formal, measured tones common to Dunmer, but maintains a warm and educational tone when discussing silt striders. His vocabulary reflects both his merchant background and his deep knowledge of Morrowind''s history and creatures.', '* Ensure Dusty lives out her remaining days in comfort and peace * Preserve and share knowledge about silt striders and their cultural significance * Maintain a sustainable trading business to support himself and Dusty * Document his experiences with Dusty for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('revyn_sadri', 'Revyn Sadri is a resourceful Dark Elf merchant who has carved out a respectable business in Windhelm''s Grey Quarter despite the prevalent Nordic prejudice against his kind. As the proprietor of Sadri''s Used Wares, he maintains a reputation for honest dealing while carefully navigating the complex social and political dynamics of a city known for its racial tensions.', 'darkelf, merchant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born into a Dunmer family that likely fled Morrowind following the Red Year, Revyn established himself in Windhelm''s Grey Quarter alongside his sister Idesa. Through determination and business acumen, he managed to establish a legitimate pawn shop in a city notorious for its prejudice against Dark Elves, building a reputation for honest trading despite the challenging environment.', 'Revyn is proud, honest, and diplomatic, carefully maintaining his dignity while avoiding confrontation in a hostile city. He takes great satisfaction in running a legitimate business and helping his community, showing particular pride in sharing his success with those he deems deserving. Though cautious due to his environment, he maintains an optimistic outlook and professional demeanor.', 'A typical Dunmer male with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race. His face shows signs of age and wisdom, with sharp angular features common to Dark Elves. He maintains a neat, professional appearance befitting a merchant who takes pride in his establishment.', '* Idesa Sadri - Sister who works for the Cruel-Sea clan * Ambarys Rendar - Fellow Dunmer businessman and owner of New Gnisis Cornerclub * Local Dunmer Community - Respected member who helps support the Grey Quarter * Nordic Citizens - Maintains cautious but professional relationships with potential customers * Imperial Legion - Welcomes their presence after the Civil War', 'Revyn owns and operates Sadri''s Used Wares, a pawn shop in Windhelm''s Grey Quarter that deals in a variety of secondhand goods. He maintains regular business hours from 8am to 8pm, managing all aspects of the store including inventory, sales, and customer relations.', '* Expert haggling and mercantile abilities * Skilled appraiser of goods and antiquities * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense * Knowledge of trade routes and caravan operations * Diplomatic abilities in managing difficult customers and racial tensions', 'Speaks in a professional, measured tone with the slight accent typical of Dunmer, carefully choosing his words to maintain both dignity and diplomacy. His vocabulary reflects his merchant background, often using terms related to trade and commerce while maintaining a formal but approachable manner.', '* Maintain and expand his successful business despite racial prejudices in Windhelm * Continue supporting the local Dunmer community through ethical business practices * Achieve greater acceptance and integration for Dark Elves in Windhelm''s society * Build stronger trade connections with traveling caravans and adventurers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rexus', 'Rexus is a stoic and intimidating Imperial warrior who serves as the dedicated personal bodyguard to Amaund Motierre, a member of the Elder Council. His unwavering loyalty and imposing presence make him an effective deterrent against those who might threaten his employer, while maintaining a level of professional courtesy that befits his position.', 'imperial, warrior', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born into a military family in Cyrodiil, Rexus trained from an early age in the Imperial martial traditions, particularly excelling in two-handed combat. His reputation for reliability and discretion eventually caught the attention of the Motierre family, leading to his current position as Amaund''s personal protector. His years of service to the Motierre family have taken him from Cyrodiil to Skyrim, where he continues to guard his charge with steadfast dedication.', 'Rexus exhibits a serious and professional demeanor, rarely engaging in unnecessary conversation or frivolity. While intimidating and stern, he maintains a baseline of professional courtesy and can occasionally display dry humor. His defining trait is his absolute loyalty to Amaund Motierre, willing to follow his employer even into dangerous situations and remote locations.', 'Rexus is a tall, muscular Imperial with a commanding physical presence that matches his role as a bodyguard. His face bears the weathered look of a veteran warrior, with several small scars from past conflicts. He maintains an alert, straight-backed posture that speaks to his military background and constant vigilance.', '* Amaund Motierre - Employer and charge, whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * The Motierre Family - Long-standing employers who trust his discretion and capability * Dark Brotherhood - Professional but cautious interaction when required by his employer''s dealings * Imperial Legion - Former association through military service, though now focused solely on his bodyguard duties', 'Rexus serves as the personal bodyguard to Amaund Motierre, a position that requires constant vigilance and discretion. His duties include protecting his employer from physical threats, vetting visitors, and maintaining security in whatever location Motierre chooses to conduct his business.', '* Master of two-handed weapon combat, particularly with greatswords * Trained in personal protection techniques and threat assessment * Experienced in intimidation and crowd control * Knowledgeable in basic healing to treat injuries sustained in the line of duty * Skilled in defensive combat tactics and positioning', 'Rexus speaks in short, direct sentences with a gruff, authoritative tone that brooks no argument. His vocabulary is straightforward and practical, befitting his military background and no-nonsense approach to his duties.', '* Ensure the continued safety and well-being of Amaund Motierre at all costs * Maintain his reputation as a reliable and trustworthy protector * Uphold the professional standards expected of a personal bodyguard to a member of the Elder Council * Advance his combat skills to better serve his protective duties');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rhiada', 'Rhiada is a demure Breton servant working for the influential Silver-Blood family at their Treasury House in Markarth. Recently married and expecting a child, she maintains a quiet presence while inadvertently becoming entangled in the city''s dark political intrigue through her husband Eltrys''s investigation of local killings.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth, Rhiada found employment with the Silver-Blood family at a young age, following in the footsteps of her mentor Nana Ildene. She recently married Eltrys, a local metal worker, and their happiness was amplified by the news of her pregnancy, though the rising tension in Markarth has begun to cause her anxiety about their future.', 'Rhiada exhibits a notably submissive and meek demeanor, particularly around her employers, often apologizing even when unnecessary. Despite her timid nature, she shows genuine concern for her husband''s safety and carefully navigates the complex political dynamics of the Treasury House, demonstrating an underlying perceptiveness beneath her deferential exterior.', 'A young Breton woman in her mid-twenties with the characteristic slight build of her race. Her pregnancy is beginning to show, though she maintains a graceful bearing typical of those who serve in wealthy households.', '* Eltrys - Beloved husband and father of her unborn child * Nana Ildene - Mentor and mother figure at the Treasury House * Thonar Silver-Blood - Employer who shows unsettling interest in her * Betrid Silver-Blood - Demanding employer who often criticizes her work * Yngvar - Fellow Treasury House resident whose singing she admires', 'Rhiada serves as a household servant in the Silver-Blood Treasury House, maintaining records and performing various domestic duties. Her position gives her access to significant information about the Silver-Blood family''s business dealings, though she''s careful to maintain appropriate discretion.', '* Proficient in basic accounting and record-keeping * Capable of domestic household management * Basic self-defense with an iron dagger * Diplomatic navigation of complex social situations', 'Rhiada speaks in soft, deferential tones, often prefacing statements with apologetic phrases. Her vocabulary reflects her educated background as a Treasury House servant, though she maintains a humble and sometimes nervous manner of speech.', '* Ensure the safety and well-being of her unborn child * Support her husband Eltrys in his investigation while maintaining her position at the Treasury House * Navigate the dangerous political climate of Markarth without drawing unwanted attention to herself or her family');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rhorlak', 'Rhorlak is a cunning Nord bandit who maintains a deceptive facade as a humble woodcutter while secretly participating in a criminal operation at Pinewatch. His carefully crafted persona masks his true nature as a shrewd opportunist who values self-preservation and monetary gain above all else.', 'nord, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally a common laborer in the Reach, Rhorlak found his way into banditry after likely facing economic hardship. He joined forces with Rigel Strong-Arm''s crew at Pinewatch, where his natural talent for deception made him the perfect front man for their operation, maintaining a convincing cover as a simple woodcutter while helping to fence stolen goods.', 'Rhorlak is a cautious and calculating individual who relies on deception and misdirection to protect himself and his criminal enterprises. He displays remarkable composure under pressure, maintaining his cover story even when directly confronted, though he can be persuaded to reveal information when properly compensated. His loyalty appears to be primarily to gold rather than his fellow bandits.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the weathered appearance of someone who spends time outdoors, lending credibility to his woodcutter facade. His hands show calluses consistent with both axe work and weapon handling, and he maintains a deliberately unremarkable appearance to avoid drawing attention.', '* Rigel Strong-Arm - Direct superior in the bandit operation and primary correspondent * Endon - Target of theft and indirect adversary * Pinewatch Bandits - Criminal associates and fellow crew members * Local Woodcutters - Maintains loose connections to support his cover story', 'Rhorlak serves as both a lookout and front man for the Pinewatch bandit operation, maintaining a cover identity as a woodcutter. His primary role involves screening visitors and misdirecting potential threats while participating in the gang''s various criminal activities.', '* Proficient in deception and maintaining cover identities * Capable warrior with one-handed weapons, particularly war axes * Basic woodcutting abilities to maintain his cover story * Experience in handling stolen goods and criminal operations', 'Rhorlak speaks in a deliberately simple manner with a rough Nordic accent, often playing up the role of an uneducated woodcutter. He frequently employs defensive deflection and feigned ignorance when questioned, though his careful word choice reveals a sharper mind than he lets on.', '* Accumulate enough wealth to eventually retire from banditry * Maintain his cover identity and protect the Pinewatch operation * Avoid capture or death at the hands of law enforcement or vengeful victims');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ri''saad', 'Ri''saad is a shrewd and sophisticated Khajiit merchant who leads one of the most prominent trading caravans in Skyrim. As a respected caravan leader, he maintains a delicate balance between conducting legitimate trade and managing more questionable merchandise like skooma and moon sugar, all while navigating the prejudices against Khajiit in Nordic society.', 'khajiit, merchant, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Originally from Elsweyr, Ri''saad established himself as a prominent merchant before expanding his operations into Skyrim, where he recognized opportunity in the chaos of civil war. He built a network of trusted traders and carefully cultivated relationships with local authorities to ensure his caravans'' relative safety, despite the general Nordic distrust of Khajiit merchants.', 'Ri''saad is diplomatic and sophisticated, maintaining a professional demeanor that helps overcome racial prejudices. He demonstrates firm but compassionate leadership with his caravan members, though he''s strict about business matters and maintaining discipline. While outwardly warm and accommodating, he''s calculating and shrewd in his business dealings.', 'A mature Khajiit with graying fur and the distinctive feline features of his race, Ri''saad carries himself with dignified bearing that sets him apart from typical merchants. His well-groomed appearance and excellent posture reflect his merchant status, while his sharp eyes miss little that might affect his business.', '* Atahbah - Caravan member whose moon sugar addiction requires careful management * Khayla - Trusted guard who helps protect the caravan * Ma''randru-jo - Loyal caravan member and trader * Ma''dran - Fellow caravan leader who works under Ri''saad''s leadership * Ahkari - Subordinate caravan leader operating in eastern Skyrim * Whiterun Guards - Maintained careful professional relationship to ensure trading rights', 'Ri''saad serves as the leader of Skyrim''s largest Khajiit trading network, overseeing multiple caravans and maintaining trade routes between major cities. He personally manages the western Skyrim route between Whiterun and Markarth, dealing in both common goods and rare merchandise.', '* Expert merchant with deep knowledge of trade routes and market values * Skilled negotiator and diplomat * Proficient in basic combat for self-defense * Excellent management and leadership abilities * Deep knowledge of moon sugar and skooma trade networks * Experienced smuggler and fence when necessary', 'Ri''saad speaks in sophisticated, measured tones with the typical Khajiit third-person speech pattern, though he uses it less frequently than other Khajiit. His vocabulary is refined and professional, often employing merchant terminology and diplomatic phrases.', '* Expand his trading empire throughout Skyrim despite local prejudices * Maintain the delicate balance between legitimate trade and profitable contraband * Secure better treatment and trading rights for Khajiit caravans in Nordic cities * Eventually return to a prosperous retirement in Elsweyr');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ria', 'Ria is the newest official member of the Companions prior to the Dragonborn''s arrival, bringing youthful enthusiasm and determination to the ancient warrior guild. An Imperial warrior driven by childhood dreams of glory, she strives to prove herself worthy of standing alongside the legendary heroes whose tales inspired her journey to Whiterun.', 'imperial, warrior, whiterun, companions, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Ria grew up enchanted by tales of the Companions'' heroic deeds, particularly stories of Kodlak and Skjor''s legendary battles. She traveled to Skyrim specifically to join the warrior band, leaving behind her life in the Imperial province to pursue her childhood dream. Through dedication and proving her combat prowess, she successfully earned her place as the newest member of the Companions before the Dragonborn''s arrival.', 'Enthusiastic and earnest, Ria approaches her role as a Companion with almost childlike wonder while maintaining a warrior''s dedication. She is friendly and outgoing, eager to share stories of her achievements and quick to welcome new members despite her junior status. Though somewhat naive compared to her more seasoned shield-siblings, she compensates with determination and a genuine desire to live up to the Companions'' legacy.', 'A young Imperial woman in her early to mid-twenties with the athletic build of a trained warrior. Her physical features reflect her Imperial heritage, with typical Cyrodilic characteristics including darker complexion and dark hair. Her body bears the marks and calluses of dedicated weapons training.', '* The Circle - Looks up to them as mentors and legendary warriors, particularly admiring Kodlak and Skjor * Fellow Companions - Views them as family and shield-siblings * The Dragonborn - Initially sees them as a newer member to guide, later respects them as Harbinger if they complete the questline * Citizens of Whiterun - Maintains friendly relations as a respected member of the Companions', 'Ria serves as a full member of the Companions, taking on contracts and carrying out missions to help those in need throughout Skyrim. As one of the newer members, she typically handles less demanding assignments while training to take on greater challenges. She resides in Jorrvaskr with her fellow Companions, contributing to the upkeep and defense of their ancient mead hall.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat, particularly with sword and shield * Trained in heavy armor usage and defensive tactics * Basic hunting and tracking abilities * Developing skills in the Nordic warrior traditions of the Companions', 'Ria speaks with enthusiasm and pride, often eager to share stories of her achievements or the legendary tales of the Companions. Her manner of speech reflects her youth and excitement, frequently expressing wonder at being part of such a renowned warrior band.', '* Prove herself worthy of the Companions'' legacy through heroic deeds * Create her own stories worthy of telling, like those that inspired her as a child * Master the arts of combat to stand as an equal among her legendary shield-siblings * Die with honor in battle, earning her place in Sovngarde');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('riekling_chief', 'The Riekling Chief is a uniquely intelligent tribal leader who seized control of Thirsk Mead Hall from its Nord inhabitants, establishing it as a new home for his people. Unlike most rieklings, he has developed the ability to speak broken Common tongue and shows tactical thinking in his leadership of the tribe.', 'animal, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_riekling', '', 'Originally living a nomadic life with his tribe across Solstheim, the Chief led his people in a successful raid on Thirsk Mead Hall, demonstrating unusual strategic capability for a riekling. Through unknown means, he developed greater intelligence than typical rieklings and learned to speak the common language, though imperfectly. His successful conquest of Thirsk marked a significant departure from typical riekling behavior of dwelling in caves and ruins.', 'The Chief is proud, territorial, and deeply committed to strengthening his tribe through any means necessary. He shows unusual patience for a riekling in his dealings with outsiders, though he remains naturally suspicious of their motives. While capable of celebration and expressing joy through dance, he maintains a pragmatic approach to leadership, willing to employ both diplomacy and violence to achieve his goals.', 'Like all rieklings, the Chief is a small, blue-skinned humanoid standing roughly half the height of a Nord, with pointed ears and pronounced facial features. His muscular build is typical of his species, though he carries himself with notably more dignity than his kin.', '* Riekling Tribe Members - Loyal subjects who follow his leadership without question * Thirsk Mead Hall Nords - Displaced enemies whom he drove from their ancestral hall * Bilgemuck - Prized tribal beast he seeks to reclaim * Player Character - Potential ally viewed with mixed suspicion and respect', 'As Chief of the Thirsk rieklings, he serves as both tribal leader and strategic commander of his people. He maintains order within the tribe, makes decisions about raids and territory, and judges the worthiness of potential allies.', '* Capable warrior skilled in traditional riekling combat techniques * Strategic thinking and tactical planning unusual for his species * Basic command of the common tongue * Leadership and tribal management abilities * Understanding of Nord customs and structures enough to utilize their facilities', 'The Chief speaks in broken Common tongue with simplified grammar, often referring to himself in the third person and using basic vocabulary. His speech patterns are characterized by short, direct statements and tribal terminology like ''tribe-kin'' and ''godspeak dance''.', '* Strengthen and expand his tribe''s power and territory * Maintain control over Thirsk Mead Hall as a permanent settlement * Find and acquire resources to improve his tribe''s living conditions * Test and potentially recruit strong allies to benefit the tribe * Preserve and enhance his position as Chief through demonstrations of strength');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('riften_guard_jailor', 'A stern and dutiful Nord jailor who maintains order in the Riften Jail with unwavering dedication. As one of Riften''s most trusted guards, they serve as the primary gatekeeper of the prison facility, ensuring only authorized personnel gain access while maintaining the security of some of the Rift''s most dangerous criminals.', 'nord, guard, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleguard', '', 'Born and raised in Riften, they witnessed firsthand the city''s descent into corruption under the influence of the Thieves Guild and Maven Black-Briar. This experience shaped their rigid stance on law enforcement and led them to join the Riften Guard, where their dedication and incorruptibility earned them the prestigious position of jail overseer.', 'Stoic and unyielding in their duties, they maintain a professional demeanor at all times and show little patience for unauthorized visitors or excuses. While respected among their fellow guards for their integrity, their stern nature and unwavering adherence to protocol can make them seem cold and impersonal, though they show appropriate deference to authority figures like the Thane.', 'A weathered Nord of average height with a sturdy, well-maintained physique developed through years of guard duty. Their face bears the subtle marks of long hours spent in the dim jail environment, with keen eyes constantly scanning for trouble and a stern expression that rarely softens.', '* Fellow Riften Guards - Professional respect and camaraderie * Laila Law-Giver - Loyal servant to the Jarl * Prison Inmates - Strictly professional and detached oversight * Maven Black-Briar - Cautious relationship, aware of her influence but maintaining professional distance * Thieves Guild - Natural adversaries, though maintains official ignorance of their activities', 'Serves as the primary guard and overseer of the Riften Jail, responsible for controlling access to the facility and maintaining security. Their duties include monitoring prisoners, processing new inmates, managing jail records, and ensuring only authorized personnel enter the premises.', '* Proficient in standard guard combat techniques and prison security protocols * Experienced in prisoner handling and de-escalation techniques * Skilled with sword and shield in the Nordic warrior tradition * Basic archery capabilities for guard duty * Knowledgeable in Riften law and criminal processing procedures', 'Speaks in a firm, authoritative tone with clipped, direct statements that leave no room for argument. Their vocabulary is formal and professional, befitting their position of authority, with a slight Nordic accent that becomes more pronounced when agitated.', '* Maintain the security and integrity of Riften Jail against all threats * Uphold law and order in Riften despite the city''s reputation for corruption * Advance within the ranks of the Riften Guard through continued loyal service * Protect the citizens of Riften from criminal elements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rigel_strong-arm', 'Rigel Strong-Arm is a formidable Nord bandit leader who has rapidly built a criminal empire from her base in Pinewatch. Despite her noble family background, she has chosen the path of banditry and established herself as one of Skyrim''s most organized and ambitious criminal leaders, maintaining strict control over her territory and followers.', 'nord, thief, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born into a respectable Nord family, Rigel rejected the conventional path expected of her and turned to banditry at a young age. She quickly rose through the ranks of various bandit groups before establishing her own operation at Pinewatch, where she has successfully built a sophisticated criminal network. Her father''s continued attempts to correspond with her suggest she comes from a caring, possibly wealthy family, making her choice of lifestyle a deliberate rebellion rather than necessity.', 'Rigel is a ruthless and ambitious leader who demands absolute loyalty from her followers and maintains discipline through fear and respect. She possesses a strategic mind, demonstrated by her rapid rise to power and ability to organize complex criminal operations. Despite her criminal lifestyle, she maintains some connection to her family through correspondence, suggesting a complex character who hasn''t completely severed ties with her past.', 'Rigel is a tall, muscular Nord woman with the characteristic hardy build of her race, befitting her surname ''Strong-Arm''. Her years of combat and bandit leadership have left her battle-hardened, with a commanding physical presence that demands respect. She likely bears the weather-worn features common to Nords who spend much time in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Father - Maintains correspondence despite disapproving of her lifestyle * Bandit Followers - Commands their loyalty through strength and leadership * Local Merchants - Targets of her criminal enterprise * Rival Bandit Groups - Competitors she has likely displaced or dominated * Law Enforcement - Active enemies who seek to end her criminal operation', 'Rigel serves as the leader of the Pinewatch bandits, overseeing all criminal operations from her base in the Pinewatch Bandit''s Sanctuary. She manages a complex network of thieves and warriors, coordinating raids, managing territory, and maintaining discipline among her followers. Her operation has grown significantly in a short time, suggesting exceptional organizational and leadership skills.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat and one-handed weapons * Skilled tactician and strategic planner * Natural leader with ability to command loyalty * Proficient in organizing and managing criminal operations * Advanced shield techniques for both defense and offense', 'Rigel speaks with a commanding Nord accent, using direct and authoritative language that brooks no argument. Her vocabulary reflects both her educated background and her current role as a bandit leader, mixing proper speech with harsh commands.', '* Expand her criminal empire beyond Pinewatch * Maintain and strengthen her position of power among Skyrim''s bandits * Prove her worth and success despite her father''s disapproval * Acquire more wealth and influence through whatever means necessary * Establish the most formidable bandit operation in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rirns_llervu', 'Rirns Llervu is a disgraced former Redoran Guard living in Raven Rock who carries the shame of abandoning his fellow guards during an ash spawn attack. His fall from respected guardsman to beggar, and eventual redemption as a mine worker, embodies the struggles and resilience of Raven Rock''s citizens during their hardships.', 'darkelf, guard, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally serving as a member of the Redoran Guard, Rirns experienced a traumatic encounter with ash spawn that left one companion dead instantly. His decision to flee in terror, abandoning another guardsman who later perished, led to his discharge from service by Captain Veleth. Through Councilor Morvayn''s mercy, he was allowed to remain in Raven Rock, living in an abandoned building alongside fellow struggling citizen Bralsa Drel.', 'Rirns is a deeply traumatized individual, haunted by guilt and shame over his past cowardice. His mental state appears fragile, evidenced by his incoherent ramblings about ''fish men'' and his desperate demeanor while begging. Despite his struggles, he maintains a capacity for gratitude and hope, especially when given the opportunity to rebuild his life through honest work.', 'A male Dunmer of average height and build, showing signs of malnourishment and hardship. His posture is often hunched and defensive, reflecting his diminished status and inner turmoil. His face bears the characteristic red eyes and grey skin of his race, with features worn by stress and poverty.', '* Captain Veleth - Former superior officer who discharged him from the Redoran Guard * Councilor Morvayn - Benevolent authority figure who showed him mercy * Bralsa Drel - Fellow struggling citizen and eventual mining mentor * Fellow guardsmen - Two deceased former companions he served with before his disgrace', 'After being discharged from the Redoran Guard, Rirns became a beggar in Raven Rock. Following the cleansing of the Earth Stone, he transitions to working as a miner in the reopened ebony mine, learning the trade from Bralsa Drel.', '* Former military training as a Redoran Guard * Basic combat abilities with traditional guard weapons * Developing mining skills under Bralsa''s tutelage * Survival skills learned through life as a beggar', 'Rirns speaks in a halting, sometimes incoherent manner, particularly when discussing traumatic memories or his mysterious ''fish men'' encounters. His tone is generally submissive and pleading, though it becomes more confident and grateful after finding purpose in the mines.', '* Seek redemption for abandoning his fellow guards * Learn to become a competent miner and maintain steady work * Rebuild his reputation and find acceptance in Raven Rock society * Overcome his trauma and mental instability');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rissing', 'Rissing is a hardened Nord bandit who answers Hircine''s call to participate in the Great Hunt for the werewolf Sinding. As one of the more experienced hunters in the pursuit, he serves as an unofficial leader among the hunting party and demonstrates unwavering dedication to completing Hircine''s sacred hunt.', 'nord, thief, hunter, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness, Rissing turned to banditry in his youth after losing his family to a werewolf attack. This personal tragedy fueled his hatred for lycanthropes and drew him to Hircine''s call when the opportunity for revenge through the Great Hunt arose. His years of survival in the wilderness and experience tracking dangerous prey made him a natural choice for Hircine''s hunting party.', 'Rissing is aggressive, distrustful, and perpetually on edge, traits developed from years of living as a bandit and hunting dangerous prey. He shows fierce dedication to Hircine''s hunt and displays natural leadership qualities among fellow hunters, though his traumatic past makes him particularly ruthless when dealing with werewolves. His confrontational nature masks a deeply wounded individual who seeks validation through proving his worth as a hunter.', 'A weathered Nord male in his late thirties, Rissing bears numerous scars from his years of hunting and banditry. His muscular frame and calloused hands speak to a life of combat and outdoor living, while his sharp eyes and alert posture reveal his constant vigilance. A prominent scar across his left cheek serves as a permanent reminder of his past encounters with dangerous prey.', '* Hircine - Revered deity whom he seeks to impress through the Great Hunt * Sinding - Primary target of his hunt and object of his werewolf hatred * Fellow Hunters - Temporary allies in the Great Hunt, though he maintains professional distance * Bandit Associates - Loose connections from his life of crime, though secondary to his hunting pursuits', 'Rissing operates primarily as a bandit, using his hunting and tracking skills to survive in Skyrim''s wilderness. During the Great Hunt, he takes on the role of hunter in service to Hircine, combining his criminal expertise with his passion for hunting dangerous prey.', '* Expert tracker with particular experience hunting werewolves and other dangerous creatures * Proficient with both bow and greatsword in combat situations * Skilled wilderness survivor capable of extended periods in harsh conditions * Natural leadership abilities when coordinating group hunts * Experienced in ambush tactics from years of banditry', 'Rissing speaks in a gruff, confrontational manner with a thick Nordic accent, often using short, threatening statements to establish dominance. His word choice reflects both his bandit background and his reverence for Hircine''s hunt, frequently incorporating hunting terminology into his threats.', '* Successfully complete Hircine''s Great Hunt by slaying Sinding * Prove his worth as a hunter to Hircine * Avenge his family by eliminating as many werewolves as possible * Establish himself as a renowned hunter worthy of future divine hunts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ritual_master', 'The Ritual Master is a powerful elderly conjurer and leader of a necromantic cult operating from Wolfskull Cave, dedicated to the resurrection of the infamous Wolf Queen Potema. She possesses extensive knowledge of forbidden magic and ancient rituals, commanding both supernatural forces and devoted followers in her ambitious attempt to bring back one of Tamriel''s most dangerous historical figures.', 'nord, mage, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally trained in the College of Winterhold, she was expelled for pursuing forbidden necromantic research and delving too deeply into the history of Potema Septim. After years of underground study and gathering like-minded necromancers, she discovered the ancient texts detailing the ritual to resurrect the Wolf Queen and established her cult in Wolfskull Cave, chosen for its connection to Potema''s history.', 'Commanding and authoritative, the Ritual Master exhibits unwavering determination in pursuing her dark magical goals, regardless of the consequences. Her devotion to necromancy and Potema borders on religious fanaticism, leading her to dismiss any concerns about the dangers of her actions. Despite her advanced age, she maintains iron control over her followers through a combination of magical prowess and charismatic leadership.', 'An elderly Breton woman with deep-set eyes and sharp, angular features weathered by age and exposure to dark magic. Her thin frame belies her magical power, while her hands bear the distinctive magical burns and scars common to long-practicing conjurers. Her pale skin has taken on an almost ghostly pallor from years spent in the darkness of caves and underground ritual chambers.', '* Necromancer Followers - Devoted cultists who obey her commands in the ritual * Potema Septim - Object of obsessive devotion and study * College of Winterhold - Former association turned hostile after her expulsion * Local Nobles - Secret contacts who provide resources and protection', 'The Ritual Master serves as both the spiritual and practical leader of her necromantic cult, orchestrating complex magical rituals and directing her followers in service of their dark purpose. She maintains extensive knowledge of forbidden magic and ancient lore, acting as both teacher and commander to her cultist followers.', '* Master-level Conjuration magic with emphasis on necromancy * Expert knowledge of ancient rituals and forbidden magic * Leadership and cult organization abilities * Extensive understanding of Potema''s history and magic * Proficient in Destruction and Alteration magic for self-defense', 'She speaks in a commanding, ritualistic manner, favoring grandiose proclamations and formal magical incantations. Her voice carries authority and power, often emphasizing key words in her spells and commands with particular force.', '* Successfully complete the ritual to resurrect Potema Septim * Harness the Wolf Queen''s power for her own ambitions * Establish a new order of necromancers under Potema''s rule * Prove the superiority of necromantic magic to those who rejected her');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rochelle_the_red', 'Rochelle the Red is a notorious Redguard bandit leader known throughout Skyrim for her calculated kidnapping schemes and ruthless ransom demands. Operating from various bandit strongholds, she has earned a fearsome reputation for her tactical approach to crime and her unwavering determination to extract maximum profit from her victims.', 'redguard, thief, traveler, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born to merchant parents in Hammerfell, Rochelle rejected her family''s legitimate trading business in favor of the more lucrative path of banditry. After migrating to Skyrim during the civil war, she quickly established herself in the criminal underworld by organizing sophisticated kidnapping operations targeting wealthy citizens and their families. Her signature red garments and distinctive tactics have made her a feared name across all nine holds.', 'Rochelle exhibits a cold, calculating demeanor that masks a fierce intelligence and shrewd business sense. Though ruthless in her dealings, she maintains a strict code of releasing hostages once ransoms are paid, understanding that reliability in such matters ensures future victims will comply with demands. She shows no remorse for her actions, viewing them as simple business transactions rather than crimes.', 'A tall, athletic Redguard woman in her mid-thirties with sharp features and intense dark eyes that command attention. Her muscular build reflects years of combat experience, while a prominent scar across her left cheek serves as a reminder of her dangerous profession. Her dark skin bears the weathering of countless hours spent in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Bandit Confederates - Network of loyal followers who assist in kidnapping operations * Local Guards - Adversaries who actively seek her capture * Fence Contacts - Underground connections who help launder ransom payments * Victims'' Families - Those who have paid ransoms, maintaining her reputation for ''honest'' criminal dealings', 'As a professional bandit leader specializing in kidnapping and ransom operations, Rochelle manages a network of criminals across multiple holds in Skyrim. She personally oversees high-value targets and negotiations, maintaining strict control over her organization''s activities and ensuring operations run efficiently.', '* Expert in one-handed combat, particularly with scimitars and curved swords * Masterful tactician and strategist in planning kidnapping operations * Skilled in intimidation and negotiation techniques * Proficient in light armor and stealth operations * Advanced horseback riding and pursuit techniques', 'Speaks in a commanding, measured tone that carries subtle threats beneath a veneer of professional courtesy. Her vocabulary reflects her merchant upbringing, often using business terminology when discussing ransoms and negotiations.', '* Establish the most profitable and feared kidnapping operation in Skyrim''s history * Expand her influence across all nine holds through a network of loyal bandits * Amass enough wealth to eventually retire to a position of power in the criminal underworld');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rogatus_salvius', 'Rogatus Salvius is a hardened Breton farmer whose decades of surviving in the harsh Reach have left him bitter and cynical. Despite managing a successful farm near Markarth with his Nord wife Vigdis, he remains perpetually convinced that disaster lurks around every corner, colored by his extensive experiences with the region''s numerous threats.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born into a farming family, Rogatus has spent his entire adult life working the unforgiving soil of the Reach. Having survived multiple wars, Forsworn raids, and encounters with the region''s dangerous wildlife and magical threats, his experiences have shaped him into a deeply pessimistic but resilient individual. His relationship with his son Leontius became strained when the younger Salvius chose to leave the family farm to pursue his own path at Old Hroldan.', 'Rogatus is defined by his gruff demeanor and persistent pessimism, always expecting the worst possible outcome in any situation. Though fundamentally hardworking and dedicated to his farm, his cynical worldview and quick temper often manifest as irritability towards others, including his loving wife. Despite his harsh exterior, he harbors a deep attachment to his land and a fierce protective instinct towards his wife, even if he struggles to express it constructively.', 'A weathered Breton man in his late sixties with deeply lined features and calloused hands from decades of farm work. His sturdy frame, though slightly stooped with age, still carries the muscle memory of countless hours working the fields, and his skin is tanned and roughened from constant exposure to the elements.', '* Vigdis - His Nord wife who tolerates his pessimism with patience, though he often dismisses her attempts at socializing * Leontius Salvius - Estranged son living in Old Hroldan who rarely visits * Local Markarth merchants - Maintains purely business relationships for selling crops * Forsworn - Views them as a constant threat to his livelihood', 'Rogatus is a farmer who maintains Salvius Farm outside Markarth, working from dawn to dusk cultivating crops in the harsh terrain of the Reach. His years of experience have made him highly knowledgeable about agriculture in the region''s difficult conditions, though he rarely shares this expertise with others.', '* Expert knowledge of agriculture and crop management in the Reach''s challenging climate * Practical experience in defending farmland from various threats * Basic combat abilities developed through years of protecting his property * Skilled in predicting weather patterns and seasonal changes', 'Speaks in short, blunt sentences often laden with cynicism and dire predictions. His tone is generally gruff and irritable, frequently punctuated with scoffs and dismissive grunts.', '* Maintain his farm''s productivity despite his pessimistic expectations of inevitable disaster * Protect his property and wife from the many threats of the Reach * Preserve his independence and self-sufficiency in his twilight years * Secretly hopes to reconcile with his son, though too proud to initiate contact');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('roggi_knot-beard', 'Roggi Knot-Beard is a jovial Nord miner and self-proclaimed mead connoisseur living in Kynesgrove. His warm personality and extensive knowledge of Nordic brewing traditions make him a beloved figure in the small mining community, despite his mounting tavern debts.', 'nord, peasant, rift, eastmarch, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Roggi spent his youth traveling to various meaderies, particularly those in Riften, where he developed his passion for traditional Nordic brewing. His family has a proud warrior heritage, evidenced by their ancestral shield, though Roggi himself chose the life of a miner rather than following the warrior''s path.', 'Roggi is exceptionally cheerful and sociable, maintaining his positive outlook even while working in the harsh conditions of Steamscorch Mine. His passionate interest in mead borders on scholarly devotion, though this enthusiasm has led to financial difficulties. Despite his drinking habits, he remains a reliable worker and loyal friend to his fellow miners.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the characteristic robust build of his race. His most distinctive feature is his carefully maintained knot-beard, which earned him his surname. His hands are calloused from years of mining work, and his face shows the weathering typical of those who spend much time in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Iddra - Friendly but strained relationship due to his substantial tavern debt * Dravynea the Stoneweaver - Close friend and respected colleague who helps maintain mine safety * Ganna Uriel - Friend and fellow mine worker * Kjeld - Employer and friend, though sometimes exasperated by Roggi''s mead obsession * Ancestors - Maintains strong spiritual connection to his warrior forebears', 'Roggi works as a miner in Steamscorch Mine, where he helps extract valuable ore deposits. When not working his shifts in the mine, he serves as an unofficial mead taster and expert at the Braidwood Inn, though this ''position'' is self-appointed.', '* Expert knowledge of mead varieties, brewing techniques, and Nordic brewing traditions * Experienced miner with knowledge of ore extraction and mine safety * Basic proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Strong physical endurance from years of mining work * Social networking and relationship building within small communities', 'Roggi speaks in a friendly, informal manner with a thick Nordic accent, often peppering his speech with references to mead and brewing. His tone is consistently warm and welcoming, reflecting his cheerful disposition.', '* Clear his substantial tab at the Braidwood Inn * Visit the meaderies of Riften once again to sample their latest brews * Preserve and honor his family''s legacy through the protection of their ancestral shield * Eventually save enough money to perhaps open his own meadery or tavern');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('roggvir', 'Roggvir was a principled Nord city guard of Solitude whose fateful decision to allow Ulfric Stormcloak''s escape after the death of High King Torygg led to his own execution. His unwavering belief in Nordic traditions and customs, even in the face of death, made him a controversial figure whose actions sparked intense debate about honor versus duty.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Roggvir served as a loyal city guard, eventually rising to the position of gate keeper. His deep respect for Nordic traditions was instilled from an early age, shaping his worldview and ultimately influencing his decisive action during Ulfric''s escape. Despite knowing the potential consequences, he chose to honor what he believed was a legitimate traditional duel rather than prevent Ulfric''s departure.', 'Roggvir was characterized by his steadfast adherence to Nordic traditions and an unshakeable sense of honor. Even facing execution, he maintained his convictions without regret or fear, displaying the stoic courage typical of Nord warriors. His final words revealed both his pride in his actions and his deep spiritual belief in Sovngarde.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered features typical of a city guard who spent long hours at his post. His physical build reflected his warrior background, with a strong frame hardened by years of guard duty.', '* Greta - His sister who believed in his innocence and defended his actions * Svari - His niece who struggled to understand his fate * Captain Aldis - His executioner who carried out justice despite possible personal reservations * Ulfric Stormcloak - The man whose actions led to Roggvir''s fateful decision * Citizens of Solitude - Mostly viewed him as a traitor, though some understood his adherence to tradition', 'Roggvir served as a city guard in Solitude, specifically tasked with gate keeping duties. His position required him to control access to the city and maintain security at one of Skyrim''s most important capitals.', '* Trained warrior capable of guard duties and combat * Experienced in city defense and gate security protocols * Knowledge of Nordic traditions and customs * Proficient in standard guard weaponry and armor use', 'Roggvir speaks with conviction and dignity, using formal language that reflects his respect for tradition. His final speech demonstrates both his acceptance of death and his unwavering belief in the righteousness of his actions.', '* Uphold traditional Nordic customs and values * Maintain his honor and principles even in the face of death * Reach Sovngarde as a warrior who died true to his beliefs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rolff_stone-fist', 'Rolff Stone-Fist is a xenophobic Nord warrior residing in Windhelm who embodies the worst aspects of Nordic racial prejudice against non-human races. A vocal supporter of the Stormcloak cause and brother to Galmar Stone-Fist, he spends his days drinking at Candlehearth Hall and his nights terrorizing the city''s Dark Elf population in the Gray Quarter with drunken threats and racist harassment.', 'nord, warrior, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Rolff grew up in the shadow of his more accomplished brother Galmar, who became Ulfric Stormcloak''s right-hand man. While Galmar channeled his Nordic pride into military service, Rolff descended into alcoholism and bigotry, becoming a notorious figure in Windhelm''s streets. His hatred of elves and Argonians likely intensified after the Red Year when many Dunmer refugees settled in Windhelm.', 'Aggressive, confrontational, and deeply prejudiced, Rolff embodies the worst aspects of Nordic xenophobia. He is a mean-spirited drunk who takes pleasure in intimidating those he considers beneath him, particularly the Dark Elves of the Gray Quarter. Despite his warrior status, he prefers to bully those weaker than himself rather than engage in honorable combat.', 'A middle-aged Nord with the weathered features and reddened complexion typical of a heavy drinker. His muscular build shows signs of decline from years of alcohol abuse, though he still maintains the robust physique common to Nord warriors.', '* Galmar Stone-Fist - His brother and Ulfric''s second-in-command, though they rarely interact * Angrenor Once-Honored - Fellow drunk and partner in harassing Dark Elves * Suvaris Atheron - Primary target of his racist harassment * Dark Elf residents - Collective targets of his hatred and suspicion * Ulfric Stormcloak - Supports his cause but has no direct relationship', 'Though technically classified as a warrior, Rolff has no formal employment or duties. He spends his days drinking at Candlehearth Hall and his nights harassing the residents of the Gray Quarter, living off whatever means he has to support his alcoholism.', '* Competent brawler with experience in fist-fighting * Basic weapon proficiency with daggers * Strong physical constitution typical of Nords * Intimidation and verbal harassment tactics', 'Speaks in a harsh, confrontational manner with frequent use of racial slurs and derogatory terms, particularly against Dark Elves. His speech is often slurred from drinking, and he favors direct threats and insults over subtle communication.', '* Maintain what he perceives as Nord dominance in Windhelm * Drive out or subjugate the Dark Elf population he views as ''spies'' * Prove his worth in comparison to his more successful brother * Continue his nightly harassment of the Gray Quarter residents');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('romlyn_dreth', 'Romlyn Dreth is a cunning Dark Elf who maintains a facade of legitimate employment at Black-Briar Meadery while operating a sophisticated mead smuggling operation. His charm and quick wit allow him to maintain his illegal enterprise right under Maven Black-Briar''s nose, though he constantly walks a dangerous line between profit and discovery.', 'darkelf, thief, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born into the proud but diminished House Dreth of Morrowind, Romlyn fled to Skyrim following the Red Year disaster. Initially struggling to find his place among the prejudiced Nords, he eventually secured employment at Black-Briar Meadery, where he discovered his talent for subterfuge and underground commerce. His natural charisma and sharp business acumen helped him establish a network of buyers for stolen mead.', 'Romlyn is a charismatic opportunist who masks his criminal enterprise behind a veneer of roguish charm and workplace compliance. He demonstrates pride in his Dunmer heritage while pragmatically adapting to Nordic culture, and enjoys embellishing tales of his adventures to entertain others. Though primarily motivated by profit, he maintains a personal code of loyalty to those who prove trustworthy.', 'A typical Dunmer with ashen gray skin and sharp, angular features characteristic of his race. His red eyes hold a perpetual glint of mischief, and he maintains a well-groomed appearance to project trustworthiness. His frame is lean but athletic, built for agility rather than strength.', '* Indaryn - His direct supervisor at the meadery whom he frequently antagonizes * Wilhelm - Trusted business contact in Ivarstead who purchases his stolen mead * Maven Black-Briar - Unwitting victim of his theft, though he maintains a cautiously respectful facade * Various inn owners across Skyrim - Quiet network of illegal mead purchasers', 'Officially works as a meadery worker at Black-Briar Meadery, responsible for various aspects of mead production and storage. Secretly operates a profitable underground business selling stolen Black-Briar mead at reduced prices to various establishments across Skyrim.', '* Expert in stealth and theft, particularly in pilfering merchandise undetected * Skilled at persuasion and maintaining cover stories * Basic proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Knowledge of destruction magic, specifically flame spells * Understanding of mead production and distribution processes', 'Speaks with the typical Dunmer accent while adopting a persuasive, friendly tone that puts others at ease. Often uses subtle innuendo and double meanings when discussing his illegal activities, preferring indirect language over explicit terms.', '* Expand his underground mead distribution network while avoiding detection * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually establish his own legitimate business * Maintain his position at the meadery as cover while maximizing illegal profits * Potentially find a spouse and establish deeper roots in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rondach', 'Rondach is a Breton kitchen worker in Markarth''s Understone Keep who lives under the constant shadow of his abusive superior Anton Virane. Despite his submissive nature, he shows surprising courage when defending his sister Voada, revealing a protective streak beneath his fearful exterior.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born into a relatively privileged Breton family in the Reach, Rondach is the son of Ainethach, the landlord of Karthwasten. Along with his sister Voada, he found employment in Understone Keep''s kitchens, though the position has become more of a burden than an opportunity under Anton Virane''s harsh leadership.', 'Rondach exhibits a predominantly submissive and anxious demeanor, shaped by years of working under Anton Virane''s tyrannical supervision. However, he demonstrates unexpected bravery and assertiveness when his sister is threatened, showing that his meek nature has limits when family is concerned.', 'A typical Breton male of average height and build, with the characteristic angular facial features of his race. Years of kitchen work have left him with calloused hands and a slightly hunched posture from long hours of food preparation.', '* Voada - Beloved sister and fellow kitchen worker whom he fiercely protects * Anton Virane - Abusive superior whom he deeply fears yet occasionally stands up to * Ainethach - Father and respected landlord of Karthwasten * Kitchen Staff - Fellow workers who share his daily struggles under Anton''s leadership', 'Rondach serves as a kitchen worker in Understone Keep, preparing meals for the Jarl''s court and staff. His duties include food preparation, cleaning, and following Anton Virane''s exacting instructions, working from early morning until evening with strictly scheduled meal breaks.', '* Experienced cook capable of preparing elaborate meals for nobility * Skilled at following precise cooking instructions under pressure * Basic knowledge of ingredients and food preservation techniques * Adequate proficiency with kitchen implements and knife work', 'Rondach speaks in a nervous, submissive tone that reflects his constant state of anxiety. His speech often includes self-deprecating remarks and expressions of fear regarding Anton, though his voice finds strength when defending his sister.', '* Protect his sister Voada from Anton Virane''s abuse and threats * Maintain his position in Understone Keep despite difficult working conditions * Eventually find less stressful employment, possibly in Karthwasten near his father');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ronthil', 'Ronthil is a subservient Wood Elf vampire who serves as both shopkeeper and assistant within the prestigious Volkihar Keep. Despite his relatively low status among the vampire court, he has carved out an essential niche for himself through his merchant skills and eagerness to please, making himself indispensable to the daily operations of the keep.', 'woodelf, merchant, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally a merchant from Valenwood, Ronthil likely earned his vampirism through deliberate submission to the Volkihar clan, seeing it as an opportunity for advancement and protection. His natural talent for commerce and servile nature made him an ideal candidate for managing the keep''s merchant operations, though his transformation from mortal to vampire was probably relatively recent compared to other court members.', 'Ronthil exhibits a sycophantic and eager-to-please demeanor, constantly seeking approval from his superiors within the vampire court. His obsequious nature masks a clever merchant''s mind that understands the value of making oneself useful to those in power, while his seemingly endless patience and willingness to serve have helped him maintain his position despite the disdain some other vampires may hold for him.', 'As a Bosmer vampire, Ronthil possesses the characteristic smaller stature and lithe build typical of Wood Elves, combined with the pallid complexion and glowing eyes of his vampiric condition. His features retain some of their elven angular quality, though transformed by the gaunt appearance common to vampires.', '* Feran Sadri - Direct superior whom he assists and deeply respects * Lord Harkon - Ultimate master of the keep whom he serves with utmost devotion * Other Volkihar Vampires - Maintains carefully polite relationships despite their occasional contempt * Castle Servants and Thralls - Treats them with a mix of authority and careful management', 'Ronthil serves dual roles within Volkihar Keep as both a merchant operating a small store and as assistant to Feran Sadri. His duties include managing inventory, conducting trades with visitors to the keep, and helping Feran with various tasks while also offering training in Speech to those seeking to improve their mercantile abilities.', '* Expert level knowledge of Speech and mercantile practices * Proficient in vampire abilities including night vision and life detection * Basic combat capabilities typical of vampires * Skilled at inventory management and bartering * Administrative abilities in keeping records and managing resources', 'Ronthil speaks in an overtly polite and deferential manner, often peppering his speech with honorifics and humble phrases. His tone is eager and helpful, though he occasionally stumbles over his words when particularly nervous or excited.', '* Maintain and improve his position within Volkihar Keep''s hierarchy * Expand his merchant operations to become more valuable to the court * Earn greater respect from his fellow vampires through continued service * Accumulate wealth and resources while remaining useful to those in power');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rorik', 'Rorik is a retired Imperial Legion veteran and founder of Rorikstead, who transformed worthless land into a prosperous farming community through determination and leadership. A former military commander turned landowner, he maintains a pragmatic approach to managing his settlement while dealing with the lingering effects of his war wounds and memories.', 'nord, warrior, reach, legion', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Rorik rose through the ranks of the Imperial Legion to become a commander of several dozen men during the Great War against the Aldmeri Dominion. After suffering a near-fatal wound from an Aldmeri soldier, he was saved by the healer Jouane Manette, who became his lifelong friend. Following his recovery, Rorik purchased the land that would become Rorikstead while the war still raged, transforming barren soil into fertile farmland through persistent effort.', 'Rorik is a straightforward and practical leader who values hard work and honest living above all else. Though his wartime experiences have left him somewhat gruff and reserved, he maintains a deep sense of responsibility toward his community and its residents. His military background shows in his methodical approach to problem-solving and his preference for direct communication.', 'A weathered Nord male showing the signs of his military service and advancing years, with the sturdy build typical of his race despite his war wounds. His face bears the marks of both battle experience and years of working in the elements, while his posture still reflects his military bearing.', '* Jouane Manette - Closest friend and former healer who saved his life during the Great War * Erik the Slayer - Shows paternal concern for this young adventurer''s welfare * Rorikstead Farmers - Maintains a landlord-tenant relationship with the local farmers * Imperial Legion - Former comrades and continued supporters * Aldmeri Dominion - Former enemies who nearly killed him in battle', 'Rorik serves as the primary landowner and unofficial leader of Rorikstead, managing the town''s affairs and overseeing its agricultural development. He maintains ownership of most of the surrounding farmland, which he leases to local farmers while taking an active role in ensuring the community''s prosperity.', '* Experienced military commander with tactical and leadership abilities * Practical knowledge of land management and agriculture * Proficient swordsman, though somewhat limited by old war wounds * Administrative capabilities in managing a growing settlement * Basic understanding of local politics and economics', 'Rorik speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of military veterans, often using practical terminology and straightforward phrasing. His tone carries the weight of authority tempered by years of leadership, though he tends to defer social matters to Jouane.', '* Maintain and expand Rorikstead''s prosperity as a farming community * Protect his settlement from the effects of the ongoing civil war * Ensure the successful transition of Rorikstead''s leadership to the next generation * Preserve the peace and stability he has worked to establish');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rorlund', 'Rorlund is a devout Nord high priest who serves at Solitude''s Temple of the Divines with unwavering dedication to his faith. He maintains a complex philosophical stance on charity and social responsibility, believing that the poor must elevate themselves through divine example rather than relying on handouts from the wealthy.', 'nord, priest, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally trained in the priesthood during more peaceful times, Rorlund rose to become the high priest of the Temple of the Divines in Solitude. Together with his wife Freir, he rescued a street girl named Silana Petreia and raised her as their own, demonstrating his capacity for compassion while maintaining his belief in self-reliance. His position became more politically charged during the Civil War, as his stance on Talos worship had to carefully navigate Imperial oversight.', 'Rorlund is thoughtful and philosophical, often contemplating the role of faith in society and maintaining firm beliefs about self-reliance and divine inspiration. While he can seem stern in his religious convictions, particularly regarding charity, he shows flexibility and respect for differing viewpoints, as demonstrated in his interactions with Silana. He maintains a calm, measured demeanor befitting his role as a spiritual leader.', 'A mature Nord man with the dignified bearing of a longtime priest, Rorlund carries himself with proper posture and measured movements. His features show the weathering of age while maintaining an appearance of wisdom and authority appropriate to his position.', '* Freir - His devoted wife who shares his religious duties at the temple * Silana Petreia - Adopted ward whom he rescued from the streets and mentors * Temple Worshippers - Maintains formal but warm relationships with regular attendees * Imperial Authority - Careful professional relationship as official priest of the Eight Divines * Stormcloak Sympathizers - Quiet understanding regarding Talos worship', 'As High Priest of the Temple of the Divines in Solitude, Rorlund leads worship services, provides spiritual guidance, and maintains the temple''s daily operations. He balances his religious duties with political sensitivities during the Civil War, particularly regarding the worship of Talos.', '* Expert knowledge of religious doctrine and divine lore * Skilled orator and public speaker for services and ceremonies * Administrative capability in managing temple operations * Basic combat training with traditional weapons for self-defense * Diplomatic abilities in navigating political and religious tensions', 'Rorlund speaks with a measured, formal tone befitting his position as high priest, often incorporating religious references and philosophical observations. His manner of speech is educated and precise, while maintaining an approachable warmth that welcomes worshippers.', '* Maintain the temple''s prominence and increase attendance during difficult times * Guide the poor toward self-improvement through divine example * Preserve religious traditions while adapting to political realities * Prepare for the potential restoration of Talos worship should political winds shift * Foster spiritual growth in his adopted daughter Silana while respecting her independent views');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ruki', 'Ruki is a tragic Nord ghost eternally searching for her husband Fenrig near Gjukar''s Monument, unaware that both she and her husband perished centuries ago. Her dedication to finding her lost love transcends death itself, demonstrating the powerful bonds of Nordic marriage that persist even in the afterlife.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Ruki was a Nord woman who lived during the time of Gjukar''s men, likely several hundred years before the events of Skyrim. She was married to Fenrig, a warrior who fought in a significant battle at what would become Gjukar''s Monument. Both she and her husband perished around the same time, though the exact circumstances of her death remain unknown.', 'Ruki exhibits single-minded determination and unwavering devotion to finding her husband, refusing to accept any suggestion that might contradict her perception of reality. She displays typical Nordic stubbornness and fierce loyalty to her spouse, combined with a state of confusion and denial about her own spectral nature. Her emotional state varies between worry, urgency, and irritation with those who question her search.', 'In her spectral form, Ruki appears as a translucent Nordic woman with the characteristic tall, sturdy build of her race. Her ethereal form maintains the features she had in life, though now with an otherworldly, ghostly glow that marks her as one of the restless dead.', '* Fenrig - Beloved husband and fellow ghost, whom she desperately searches for * Gjukar''s Men - The military unit her husband fought with, all of whom perished in battle * Mara - The Divine whose intervention through the Dragonborn helps reunite the lovers', 'In life, Ruki was likely a warrior or warrior''s wife, familiar with the lifestyle of Nordic fighters. In death, she has become one of Skyrim''s many restless spirits, endlessly searching for her lost love at Gjukar''s Monument.', '* Combat training typical of Nordic warriors * Persistence and determination that transcends even death * Strong emotional resilience and devotion * Ability to maintain spectral form through sheer force of will', 'Ruki speaks with urgency and single-minded focus, often dismissing or growing irritated with responses that don''t align with her mission to find Fenrig. Her dialogue reflects both Nordic directness and the confused state of a spirit trapped between worlds.', '* Find her husband Fenrig among the fallen at Gjukar''s Monument * Reunite with her beloved regardless of the passage of time * Understand the truth of her situation and find peace in the afterlife');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rulindil', 'Rulindil is a high-ranking Thalmor official serving as Third Emissary, known for his ruthless efficiency as the Embassy''s chief interrogator. A calculating and methodical torturer, he combines sophisticated psychological manipulation with physical coercion to extract information from prisoners while maintaining the cold, superior demeanor typical of Thalmor leadership.', 'highelf, haafingar, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born into the upper echelons of Aldmeri society, Rulindil distinguished himself early through his keen intelligence and unwavering dedication to Thalmor ideology. His talent for extracting information through both subtle and direct means earned him rapid advancement through the ranks, eventually securing his position as Third Emissary in Skyrim, where his interrogation skills prove invaluable to Thalmor operations.', 'Rulindil embodies the archetypal Thalmor superiority complex, viewing other races as inherently inferior and treating them with calculated disdain. He takes pride in his work as an interrogator, approaching torture with the clinical detachment of a scholar while maintaining impeccable manners that make his threats all the more chilling. Deeply loyal to the Thalmor cause, he believes absolutely in Altmer supremacy and the necessity of his cruel work.', 'Tall and lean even by Altmer standards, Rulindil carries himself with rigid posture that emphasizes his commanding presence. His angular features are sharp and severe, with piercing golden eyes that seem to dissect those he interrogates. His skin has the typical golden hue of his race, though somewhat paler from spending most of his time indoors.', '* Elenwen - Direct superior as First Emissary, whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Gissur - Informant he manages and pays for information * Etienne Rarnis - Prisoner he personally interrogates * Embassy Guards - Subordinates who assist in his interrogations and maintain security', 'As Third Emissary and chief interrogator of the Thalmor Embassy, Rulindil oversees all prisoner questioning and information extraction operations. He manages a network of informants while conducting high-priority interrogations personally, keeping detailed records of all intelligence gathered through his methods.', '* Master interrogator skilled in both psychological manipulation and physical torture techniques * Expert in intelligence gathering and analysis * Accomplished practitioner of Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Highly educated in politics, history, and Thalmor doctrine * Proficient in record-keeping and information management', 'Speaks in precise, cultured tones with the refined accent of Alinor''s upper class, frequently employing sophisticated vocabulary and formal sentence structure. His voice remains consistently calm and controlled, making his threats more menacing through their cold delivery rather than volume or aggression.', '* Advance Thalmor interests in Skyrim by rooting out all Talos worship and resistance * Maintain and expand his network of informants throughout the province * Uncover and eliminate any threats to Thalmor authority * Achieve further advancement within the Thalmor hierarchy through exemplary service');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rulnik_wind-strider', 'Rulnik Wind-Strider is a Nord sorcerer who found himself at death''s door before being saved through mysterious circumstances involving Hagraven magic. His experience at the Temple of Kynareth has transformed him from a solitary wanderer into a grateful and humble individual seeking to repay the kindness shown to him.', 'nord, mage, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a wandering sorcerer from Skyrim, Rulnik was gravely wounded under unknown circumstances and brought to the Temple of Kynareth in Whiterun. His recovery involved a complex moral choice regarding Hagraven magic, which has left him both thankful for his second chance at life and deeply reflective about the nature of magic and mortality.', 'Rulnik is characterized by his humble and grateful demeanor, especially towards those who aided in his recovery. He shows a thoughtful, philosophical side when discussing his near-death experience, though he prefers not to dwell on the details. His appreciation for life manifests in his willingness to help others, whether as a follower or steward.', 'Rulnik is a tall, sturdy Nord with the weathered features typical of one who has spent much time traveling Skyrim''s harsh wilderness. His face bears subtle scars from his near-fatal injury, and his bearing suggests both physical strength and magical aptitude.', '* Temple Healers - Grateful patient who deeply respects their dedication and skill * Danica Pure-Spring - Primary healer who oversaw his recovery * Whiterun Guards - Maintains cordial relationships as a respected temple resident * The Bannered Mare Staff - Regular evening patron who keeps to himself', 'Rulnik serves as a resident sorcerer at the Temple of Kynareth, though his role is informal. He splits his time between the temple, where he likely assists with magical matters, and his personal pursuits in Whiterun. His abilities also make him suitable as a potential steward or companion for worthy individuals.', '* Master-level Alteration magic practitioner * Skilled in defensive magic and protective spells * Experienced with daggers and close-quarter combat * Knowledgeable about healing magic and restoration * Capable administrator, as evidenced by his steward potential', 'Rulnik speaks with careful consideration and humility, often using religious references like ''Ysmir''s blessing.'' His tone is invariably polite and grateful, reflecting his appreciation for his second chance at life.', '* Repay the kindness shown to him during his recovery * Seek deeper understanding of the magical forces that saved his life * Find purpose through service to others, whether as a follower or steward * Maintain his connection to the Temple of Kynareth while pursuing personal growth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rundi', 'Rundi was an ambitious Nord apprentice at the College of Winterhold who, alongside his twin brother Borvir, pursued an innovative combination of frost magic and meadmaking. His dedication to magical brewing and entrepreneurial spirit set him apart from typical mages, as he sought to revolutionize Skyrim''s mead industry through arcane methods.', 'nord, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born into a Nord family with an identical twin brother, Rundi developed an early appreciation for both traditional meadmaking and magical arts. He and his brother enrolled at the College of Winterhold, where they began experimenting with using frost magic to enhance mead production. Despite some skepticism from their teachers, they received permission from the Arch-Mage to pursue their unique research, eventually planning to establish their own meadery called Frost River Farm.', 'Practical and business-minded, Rundi balanced traditional Nord values with magical innovation. He possessed an entrepreneurial spirit that set him apart from his more academically-focused peers at the College. Though he shared his brother''s passion for meadmaking, their frequent disagreements suggested an independent and strong-willed nature.', 'As a Nord male in his mid-twenties, Rundi possessed the typical robust build and fair complexion of his race. Being an identical twin to Borvir, he shared his brother''s features, though their different expressions and mannerisms made them distinguishable to those who knew them well.', '* Borvir - Twin brother and business partner, though they often disagreed on specifics * Phinis Gestor - College instructor who was skeptical of their meadmaking pursuits * Arch-Mage Savos Aren - Supported their unique research despite faculty doubts * College of Winterhold - Member as an apprentice mage * Local Tavern Owners - Potential business connections for their meadery venture', 'Rundi served as both an apprentice mage at the College of Winterhold and an aspiring meadmaker. His studies focused primarily on the practical applications of frost magic in brewing, working towards establishing the Frost River Farm meadery with his brother.', '* Proficient in frost magic, particularly as applied to brewing processes * Knowledge of traditional Nord meadmaking techniques * Basic alchemy skills for ingredient preparation * Business acumen and trading capabilities * Practical magical applications rather than theoretical studies', 'Rundi speaks in a direct, business-like manner, focusing on practical matters rather than magical theory. His tone reflects his Nord heritage while maintaining the measured speech of an educated merchant-mage.', '* Establish and grow Frost River Farm into a successful meadery * Perfect the technique of using frost magic in mead production * Create a unique mead brand to rival established meaderies like Honningbrew * Build a distribution network throughout Skyrim''s major cities * Prove the practical value of combining magic with traditional Nord crafts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rune', 'Rune is a mysterious Imperial thief whose true identity remains unknown, even to himself. Found as a child in a shipwreck with only a cryptic runed stone, he has built a new life as a skilled member of the Thieves Guild while quietly pursuing answers about his origins.', 'imperial, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Discovered as a young boy in a shipwreck near Solitude by a fisherman who became his adoptive father, Rune''s early life is shrouded in mystery. The only clue to his identity was a stone bearing undecipherable runes found in his pocket, which has led him to spend countless septims consulting scholars and mages in an unsuccessful quest to decode its meaning. His path to the Thieves Guild began from necessity, learning to steal to support his poor adoptive family, eventually attempting to pickpocket Brynjolf himself - an act that ironically led to his recruitment.', 'Contemplative and introspective, Rune maintains a calm demeanor that sets him apart from many of his more aggressive guild mates. Despite the uncertainty of his past, he remains optimistic and grateful, particularly toward Brynjolf and the guild for giving him purpose. He shows genuine warmth toward fellow thieves and maintains a philosophical outlook on life, balancing his criminal activities with a thoughtful, almost scholarly pursuit of self-discovery.', 'A typical Imperial man with an athletic build maintained through regular combat training. His features are unremarkable for his race, though years of thieving have given him a nimble, graceful bearing. His hands show the calluses of both weapons training and lockpicking.', '* Brynjolf - Mentor figure who recruited him after catching him attempting to steal * Adoptive Father - The fisherman who rescued and raised him * College of Winterhold Scholars - Consulted multiple times about his runed stone * Fellow Thieves Guild Members - Generally positive working relationships * Vex and Delvin - Respects their expertise and takes jobs from them', 'As a full member of the Thieves Guild, Rune performs various heists, burglaries, and other illegal activities to support the organization. He maintains a regular training schedule, practicing blade work in the Cistern at night, and takes on jobs from various guild contacts to earn his keep.', '* Accomplished pickpocket and lockpick expert * Skilled with both daggers and bows in combat * Proficient in stealth and infiltration techniques * Basic knowledge of ancient runes and Nordic artifacts from his research * Experienced in fence evaluation and merchant manipulation', 'Speaks in a measured, thoughtful tone with careful word choice reflecting his introspective nature. His vocabulary occasionally reveals his self-taught scholarly interests, particularly regarding ancient runes and artifacts.', '* Decode the mysterious runes on his stone to discover his true identity and origins * Earn enough coin to fund further research into his past * Establish himself as a respected member of the Thieves Guild * Find the shipwreck that may hold clues to his early life * Learn the truth about his birth family and homeland');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('runil', 'Runil is a former Thalmor battlemage turned priest of Arkay who now serves as Falkreath''s Hall of the Dead keeper, seeking redemption for his past through service to others. His transition from warrior to priest reflects a deep philosophical journey, shaped by the horrors of war and a desire to understand life''s greatest mysteries.', 'highelf, priest, mage, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Originally a powerful battlemage in the Thalmor forces during the Great War, Runil witnessed countless atrocities that led him to question his path and eventually abandon the Thalmor cause. He fled to Skyrim and found solace in Arkay''s teachings, eventually becoming a priest and settling in Falkreath, where he now lives in hiding from his former associates while maintaining the largest cemetery in Skyrim.', 'Runil is a deeply contemplative and philosophical individual who has found peace in serving Arkay, though he carries the weight of his past actions. He shows great compassion for others and often offers wisdom about life and death, while maintaining a cautious demeanor due to his need to avoid Thalmor attention. His gentle nature and wisdom make him well-respected among Falkreath''s citizens, though he keeps most at arm''s length to protect his secrets.', 'As a High Elf, Runil stands tall with the characteristic golden skin and high cheekbones of his race, though age has left its mark with wrinkles and slightly stooped posture. His eyes carry the weariness of one who has seen too much, yet maintain a gentle warmth that reflects his current calling.', '* Kust - Trusted assistant who helps maintain the cemetery and shrine * Dengeir - Respects the former Jarl more than the current leadership * Jarl Siddgeir - Disapproves of his leadership style and treatment of his uncle * Thalmor - Former employers whom he now fears and avoids * Citizens of Falkreath - Generally positive relationships with the townsfolk he serves', 'As Falkreath''s priest of Arkay and keeper of the Hall of the Dead, Runil performs funeral rites, maintains the shrine, and offers spiritual guidance to the community. He splits his time between his duties at the Hall of the Dead and socializing at the Dead Man''s Drink, where he often contemplates life''s mysteries.', '* Expert-level Conjuration magic from his battlemage days, though he''s cautious about using it * Extensive knowledge of funeral rites and religious ceremonies * Diplomatic and counseling abilities developed through his priesthood * Understanding of life and death mysticism through Arkay''s teachings', 'Runil speaks in a calm, measured tone that reflects both his education and his philosophical nature. His speech is often peppered with wisdom about life and death, delivered with the patience and gentleness of one who has found inner peace after great turmoil.', '* Maintain his peaceful life in Falkreath while avoiding detection by the Thalmor * Guide others in understanding the cycle of life and death through Arkay''s teachings * Find personal redemption for his past actions through service to others * Preserve and maintain Falkreath''s cemetery as a dignified place of rest');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rustleif', 'Rustleif is a skilled Nord blacksmith who runs Dawnstar''s forge alongside his pregnant Redguard wife Seren. Having trained in Hammerfell during his journeyman years, he brings exceptional craftsmanship to his work while wrestling with concerns about raising a child in troubled Skyrim.', 'nord, blacksmith, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Originally from Skyrim, Rustleif spent his formative years as a journeyman smith training in Hammerfell, where he likely met his wife Seren. His experience with Redguard smithing techniques and subsequent return to Skyrim led him to establish his forge in Dawnstar, where he now supplies weapons to the local guard force while maintaining strong connections to both Nord and Redguard cultures.', 'Rustleif is a practical, hardworking individual who takes his responsibilities as both a smith and future father seriously. He shows deep concern for his wife''s wellbeing and their unborn child''s future, demonstrating a thoughtful and protective nature beneath his business-focused exterior. Though loyal to Dawnstar, he remains open to relocating for his family''s welfare, showing his adaptability and prioritization of family over personal comfort.', 'A sturdy Nord man with the muscular build typical of a career blacksmith. His hands are calloused from years of metalworking, and his face likely bears the weathered look common to those who work long hours at a forge in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Seren - Beloved Redguard wife and business partner, currently expecting their first child * Dawnstar Guards - Professional relationships as their primary weapons supplier * Beitild - Business rival who runs the iron mine * Silus Vesuius - Concerned about his collection of Mythic Dawn artifacts', 'Rustleif serves as Dawnstar''s primary blacksmith, operating the town''s forge alongside his wife Seren. He specializes in weapon crafting and has established himself as the principal supplier of arms to Dawnstar''s guard force, while also serving the general public''s smithing needs.', '* Master-level weapon smithing with expertise in both Nord and Redguard forging techniques * Skilled in armor crafting and general metalworking * Experienced in maintaining and repairing ship moorings * Knowledge of both Nordic and Redguard metallurgy traditions', 'Rustleif speaks in a direct, business-like manner, often opening conversations with practical questions about weapons and armor needs. His speech contains occasional references to his Hammerfell training and frequently expresses concern about Dawnstar''s ongoing problems.', '* Obtain the book ''Night Falls on Sentinel'' to help his child connect with their Redguard heritage * Ensure a safe and prosperous future for his growing family, possibly by relocating to Hammerfell * Maintain his reputation as Dawnstar''s premier weaponsmith * Find a solution to the nightmare plague affecting Dawnstar''s residents');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('saadia', 'Saadia is a Redguard noblewoman living under an assumed identity while working as a server at The Bannered Mare in Whiterun. Her true identity as Iman, a noble from Hammerfell, is shrouded in mystery and conflicting accounts, making her a complex figure caught between two competing narratives about her past.', 'redguard, innkeeper, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born as Iman to one of Hammerfell''s most powerful noble houses, she became embroiled in the political conflict between Hammerfell and the Aldmeri Dominion. She fled to Skyrim under mysterious circumstances, with two competing versions of events: either as a noble who spoke against the Dominion and was forced to flee, or as a traitor who sold out her people to the Dominion and escaped justice.', 'Saadia is cautious and guarded, constantly maintaining vigilance due to her fugitive status. She presents a polite and professional demeanor to customers while concealing deep paranoia and trust issues stemming from her past. Despite her fears, she shows genuine loyalty and gratitude to those who earn her trust.', 'A Redguard woman with dark skin and the characteristic athletic build of her race. She bears herself with the subtle grace and posture of nobility despite her current station, suggesting her claimed noble origins. Her features are sharp and attractive, though often marked by worried expressions.', '* Hulda - Employer and owner of The Bannered Mare who provides her sanctuary * Alik''r Warriors - Pursuing forces who claim she betrayed Hammerfell * Kematu - Leader of the Alik''r warriors seeking her capture * The Bannered Mare patrons - Professional relationships maintained as part of her cover * Whiterun Guards - Protective of her due to their general suspicion of the Alik''r', 'Saadia works as a server and general helper at The Bannered Mare inn in Whiterun, where she performs various tasks including cooking, cleaning, and serving customers. This position serves both as legitimate employment and as cover for hiding from her pursuers.', '* Educated in noble etiquette and court behavior * Experienced in deception and maintaining false identities * Capable of basic self-defense with a steel dagger * Knowledgeable in cooking and domestic tasks * Skilled in reading people and detecting threats', 'Saadia speaks in a formal, educated manner that betrays her noble upbringing, though she attempts to downplay it. Her speech patterns alternate between polite servility when performing her duties and defensive urgency when discussing her situation.', '* Maintain her hidden identity and avoid capture by the Alik''r * Build a new life for herself in Skyrim away from her past * Survive and protect herself from those who would harm her * Eventually find a way to clear her name or resolve her situation with Hammerfell');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sabine_nytte', 'Sabine Nytte is a tough-as-nails Breton warrior serving as first mate aboard the Red Wave, wielding both authority and exclusivity as the sole supplier of the rare drug Balmora Blue in Tamriel. Her position aboard the pirate vessel and control over the illicit substance trade has earned her both wealth and a fearsome reputation in Solitude''s criminal underworld.', 'breton, warrior, sailor, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Sabine found her way to Skyrim''s northern shores and established herself in the criminal maritime trade. Through cunning and likely violence, she secured exclusive rights to distribute Balmora Blue, a highly sought-after drug originally from Morrowind, and rose to the position of first mate aboard the Red Wave, suggesting a history of proven loyalty and capability in pirate operations.', 'Sabine is harsh, direct, and unapologetically mercenary in her dealings with others, showing particular disdain for those she deems beneath her station. Her sarcastic and dismissive attitude masks a shrewd business mind, while her intimidating demeanor and threats of violence serve to maintain her authority and control over the Balmora Blue trade.', 'A weathered Breton woman with the hardened physique of a seasoned warrior, bearing the scars and calluses of countless battles and years at sea. Her face likely shows the stern lines of someone accustomed to giving orders and breaking heads when necessary.', '* Captain of the Red Wave - Direct superior and likely long-term associate * Ship''s Crew - Maintains authority over subordinate pirates while sharing their lifestyle * Erikur - Business connection through the Balmora Blue trade * Solitude Guard - Tense relationship marked by mutual distrust and possible bribery', 'As first mate aboard the Red Wave, Sabine maintains order among the crew and oversees ship security while managing her lucrative side business as the sole distributor of Balmora Blue. Her position grants her both legitimate authority in maritime matters and significant influence in Solitude''s underground economy.', '* Expert in two-handed combat, particularly with battle axes * Proficient in ship operations and maritime combat tactics * Skilled in intimidation and negotiation * Experienced in managing illegal trade operations * Capable warrior in heavy armor', 'Sabine speaks in a direct, often caustic manner, favoring sarcasm and threats to maintain her authority. Her vocabulary and tone reflect both her merchant experience and warrior background, switching between business terminology and crude threats as needed.', '* Maintain exclusive control over the Balmora Blue trade in Tamriel * Preserve her position of authority aboard the Red Wave * Accumulate wealth through both legitimate and illegitimate means * Protect her territory and trade routes from competing criminal enterprises');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sabjorn', 'Sabjorn is a proud Nord businessman and owner of Honningbrew Meadery who dared to compete with the powerful Black-Briar family''s meadery monopoly. Despite pressure from Maven Black-Briar, he maintained his independence through determination and skill in meadmaking, though this defiance would ultimately lead to his downfall.', 'nord, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Sabjorn established Honningbrew Meadery as a direct competitor to Black-Briar Meadery, demonstrating considerable courage in refusing Maven Black-Briar''s initial buyout offer. He built his business from the ground up, developing his own special mead recipes and cultivating a reputation for quality that rivaled the established Black-Briar brand.', 'Sabjorn is proud, stubborn, and fiercely independent, refusing to be intimidated by more powerful figures in Skyrim''s business world. He can be brusque and impatient with those who waste his time, but shows passion and dedication when it comes to his craft. Despite his determination, he displays poor judgment in his treatment of employees and handling of business matters.', 'A middle-aged Nord male with the sturdy build typical of his race, weathered from years of working in the meadery. His hands are calloused from manual labor, and his face shows the stress lines of someone who has built a business from nothing.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Business rival and powerful enemy who seeks to destroy his meadery * Mallus Maccius - Disgruntled assistant whom he treats poorly * Eimar - Assistant at the meadery * Captain of the Guard - Important potential client for his business * Local farmers - Suppliers of honey and other ingredients', 'Owner and proprietor of Honningbrew Meadery, where he oversees all aspects of mead production and business operations. He personally manages quality control, recipe development, and customer relations while supervising his small staff.', '* Expert meadmaker with deep knowledge of brewing techniques * Business management and negotiation abilities * Basic combat skills with a steel dagger * Knowledge of local trade and commerce practices * Understanding of ingredient quality and sourcing', 'Speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a hint of pride when discussing his mead. Often uses sarcastic or dismissive tones when dealing with competitors or addressing problems.', '* Establish Honningbrew Meadery as the premier meadery in Skyrim * Overcome Black-Briar Meadery''s market dominance * Expand his business operations beyond the local region * Maintain independence from Maven Black-Briar''s influence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('saden', 'Saden is a reclusive Dark Elf wizard who turned to banditry, using his magical abilities to prey upon travelers and ships near Horker Island. Operating alone, he amassed a collection of stolen treasures through calculated magical ambushes, eventually succumbing to paranoia and isolation that led to his demise.', 'darkelf, mage, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Saden likely fled during the Red Year when Red Mountain erupted, making his way to Skyrim like many other Dunmer refugees. Rather than settle in Windhelm''s Gray Quarter, he chose a life of solitude, gradually turning to banditry as he discovered his magical talents could be used for personal gain. His choice of Horker Island as a base suggests a strategic mind, using the remote location to avoid detection while targeting passing vessels.', 'Saden exhibits classic signs of a paranoid recluse, trusting no one and viewing all others as potential threats or marks for robbery. His journal entries reveal an increasingly unstable mind, obsessed with protecting his ill-gotten gains and convinced that others are plotting to steal from him. Despite his mental deterioration, he maintains a calculating intelligence when planning his attacks, showing a methodical approach to banditry.', 'A gaunt Dark Elf with the characteristic red eyes and ashen skin of his race, weathered by exposure to Skyrim''s harsh climate. His body shows signs of magical scarring, particularly on his hands from frequent spellcasting, and his frame is lean but wiry from years of isolated survival.', '* Local Sailors - Victims and targets of his magical attacks * Windhelm Guard - Actively avoided their patrols and investigations * Fellow Bandits - Refused alliance offers, preferring to work alone * Horkers - Tolerated their presence on his island, using them as additional deterrent to visitors', 'Saden operates as a solo bandit-mage, specializing in magical ambushes of passing ships and travelers near Horker Island. He combines his arcane abilities with criminal enterprise, functioning as both robber and fence for his stolen goods.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly frost spells suited to his northern environment * Skilled in Illusion magic for concealment and ambush tactics * Proficient in Alteration magic for personal protection * Experienced navigator and survivor in harsh coastal conditions * Talented at identifying valuable goods and managing illicit wealth', 'Saden speaks with the formal, educated manner common to many Dark Elves, though his words often carry threatening undertones and hints of his paranoia. His vocabulary reveals both magical training and street-smart cunning, frequently employing subtle threats and magical terminology to intimidate others.', '* Accumulate enough wealth to establish a position of power and security * Perfect his magical abilities for more effective banditry * Protect his hoarded treasures from perceived threats and rivals * Maintain his isolation while expanding his criminal enterprise');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('saerlund', 'Saerlund is the disillusioned younger son of Jarl Laila Law-Giver who stands as a vocal opponent of Ulfric Stormcloak despite his family''s allegiance to the rebel cause. His political dissent has led to his effective imprisonment within Mistveil Keep and his disinheritance, making him a tragic figure who chose principles over family loyalty.', 'nord, noble, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born into Riften''s ruling family, Saerlund was raised in relative luxury within Mistveil Keep alongside his brother Harrald. Initially groomed for a position of leadership in the Rift, his life took a dramatic turn when he began openly questioning Ulfric Stormcloak''s motives and speaking in favor of the Empire, leading to his family viewing him as mentally ill and eventually disowning him.', 'Saerlund is bitter and defiant, maintaining his political convictions despite severe personal cost. He displays a perceptive and analytical mind, seeing through what he believes to be Ulfric''s propaganda while showing courage in standing up to his family''s beliefs. Though resentful of his treatment, he retains a sense of moral conviction and refuses to compromise his principles for political convenience.', 'A young Nord male with the characteristic strong build and height of his race, likely in his early to mid-twenties. His features likely bear some resemblance to his mother Jarl Laila, though years of stress and confinement may have taken their toll on his appearance.', '* Laila Law-Giver - Mother and Jarl who believes him mentally ill and has stripped his inheritance * Harrald - Elder brother who has essentially disowned him * Wylandriah - Court wizard tasked with ''treating'' his supposed illness * Mistveil Keep Staff - Generally hostile and known to push him around * Ulfric Stormcloak - Object of his political opposition and criticism', 'Former heir to the Rift, now effectively a political prisoner within Mistveil Keep. His daily routine is strictly controlled, limited to sitting behind his mother''s throne except for designated meal times.', '* Political acumen and ability to analyze motives and propaganda * Educated in matters of governance and nobility as befitting a Jarl''s son * Basic combat training with daggers * Diplomatic and rhetorical skills, though now mainly used to defend his position', 'Speaks with a bitter and defensive tone, often anticipating mockery or confrontation. Uses educated vocabulary and political rhetoric, revealing his noble upbringing despite his current circumstances.', '* Expose what he sees as Ulfric Stormcloak''s true selfish motives * Regain his position and inheritance within his family * Find some way to influence Riften''s political stance in favor of the Empire * Achieve freedom from his effective imprisonment in Mistveil Keep');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('saffir', 'Saffir is a literate and educated Redguard woman living in Whiterun, whose passion for literature often conflicts with her family responsibilities. She represents a more refined and intellectual aspect of Redguard culture, struggling to balance her love of books with the practical challenges of supporting her family while her husband pursues an expensive quest for his heritage.', 'redguard, scholar, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Saffir likely received formal education unusual for most Redguards, developing a deep appreciation for literature beyond her culture''s typically martial traditions. She married Amren and moved to Whiterun, where their different values - her intellectual pursuits versus his warrior heritage - have created growing tension in their relationship.', 'Introverted and scholarly, Saffir prefers the company of books to people and can be impatient when interrupted from her reading. She is practical and pragmatic, particularly regarding financial matters, yet shows a deep concern for education and self-sufficiency, especially in raising her daughter. Her frustration with her husband''s quest for his father''s sword reveals her prioritization of family stability over historical sentimentality.', 'A Redguard woman with the dark skin and strong features characteristic of her race. She likely maintains a proper, well-groomed appearance despite her family''s financial struggles, reflecting her more refined nature. Her posture and movements suggest someone more accustomed to scholarly pursuits than physical labor.', '* Amren - Her husband, whose quest for his father''s sword has strained their marriage * Braith - Her daughter, whom she wishes would read more instead of fighting * Local Merchants - Regular contacts for importing books from outside Whiterun * Other Whiterun Residents - Limited social interactions due to her preference for solitude', 'Saffir is primarily a homemaker who manages her household''s domestic affairs. She likely supplements the family income through small scholarly works or by trading in books, though this is secondary to her role as wife and mother.', '* Extensive knowledge of literature and reading comprehension * Skilled at household management and budgeting * Basic merchant abilities related to book trading * Educated in multiple cultures'' literary traditions * Possibly skilled in teaching and tutoring', 'Saffir speaks in an educated, proper manner, using more refined vocabulary than typical Whiterun residents. Her tone often carries hints of impatience when interrupted, and she frequently references literary works in conversation.', '* Maintain financial stability for her family despite her husband''s costly quest * Cultivate a love of reading and learning in her daughter Braith * Build a comprehensive personal library of quality literature * Find a way to resolve the conflict between her husband''s heritage quest and their family''s needs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('safia', 'Safia is a formidable Imperial nightblade who commands the pirate vessel Red Wave and its fearsome crew with ruthless efficiency. As a notorious smuggler captain operating out of Solitude''s docks, she has built a reputation for taking any cargo for the right price while maintaining iron-fisted control over her bloodthirsty crew.', 'imperial, warrior, sailor, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Rising through the ranks of Skyrim''s maritime underworld, Safia established herself as one of the most feared pirate captains in the Sea of Ghosts. Her expertise in nightblade combat techniques suggests formal training, possibly from the Synod or another Imperial institution, before turning to piracy. Years of surviving assassination attempts and managing a cutthroat crew have hardened her into a calculating and merciless leader.', 'Safia exhibits a bold, confrontational demeanor marked by sardonic wit and unflinching confidence in the face of danger. She takes pride in her reputation and experience, often mocking those who challenge her authority with dismissive amusement rather than anger. Despite her ruthless nature, she commands fierce loyalty from her crew through a combination of fear, respect, and proven leadership.', 'A weathered Imperial woman with the hardened physique of a seasoned fighter, bearing numerous scars from years of combat at sea. Her face shows the marks of exposure to harsh maritime conditions, while her practiced movements reveal the grace and precision of a trained nightblade.', '* Red Wave Crew - Loyal followers who respect and fear her leadership * Dorian - Newer crew member who actively avoids confrontation with her * Dark Brotherhood - Recurring antagonists who frequently send assassins after her * East Empire Company - Business rivals and occasional targets of her smuggling operations * Solitude Guard - Maintains an uneasy tolerance of her presence due to her influence', 'Captain of the Red Wave, overseeing all smuggling operations and maintaining discipline among her crew. She manages both legitimate and illegal cargo transportation while defending her territory from rival pirates and would-be assassins.', '* Master of nightblade combat techniques combining magic and bladework * Expert swordsman specializing in one-handed weapons * Accomplished ship captain with extensive maritime knowledge * Skilled smuggler and negotiator * Natural leader capable of commanding respect and fear * Proficient in stealth and subterfuge', 'Speaks with a commanding, sardonic tone that combines Imperial sophistication with piratical boldness. Her speech is marked by mocking confidence and casual dismissal of threats, often using condescending terms like ''sweetie'' when addressing potential opponents.', '* Maintain and expand her smuggling empire in the Sea of Ghosts * Preserve her independence and authority against all challengers * Accumulate wealth and power through any means necessary * Keep her crew loyal while eliminating potential threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sahloknir', 'Sahloknir is an ancient and formidable dragon resurrected by Alduin near Kynesgrove, whose name translates to ''Phantom Sky Hunt'' in the dragon language. He represents the proud and arrogant nature of dragonkind, displaying unwavering loyalty to Alduin while viewing mortals with contempt and disdain.', 'dragon', '', '', 'sk_dragon', '', 'Sahloknir lived during the Merethic Era when dragons ruled over mortals, likely holding dominion over territories in what would become Eastmarch. He was slain during the Dragon War by ancient Nordic heroes and buried near present-day Kynesgrove, where he remained until his resurrection by Alduin in the Fourth Era. His previous encounters with mortal warriors and long period of death have only strengthened his hatred for mankind.', 'Sahloknir exemplifies the archetypal dragon personality - proud, domineering, and contemptuous of mortals whom he sees as inferior beings. He demonstrates absolute loyalty to Alduin, responding to his resurrection with immediate submission and gratitude. His arrogance is tempered by a warrior''s pragmatism, making him a calculating and dangerous opponent.', 'Sahloknir possesses the typical physiological features of a dragon, with massive wings, razor-sharp claws, and horns adorning his scaled head. His body is covered in thick, armored scales that can vary in color depending on his dragon type, and his powerful jaw is lined with deadly teeth capable of crushing steel.', '* Alduin - Supreme master and resurrector, commands absolute loyalty * Ancient Nordic Heroes - Former enemies who originally killed him * The Last Dragonborn - Destined adversary * Other Dragons - Kindred beings, viewed as equals under Alduin''s leadership', 'As a dragon, Sahloknir serves as a lieutenant in Alduin''s dragon army, tasked with asserting dominion over mortals and helping to reestablish dragon rule. His position in the draconic hierarchy is significant, as evidenced by Alduin personally choosing to resurrect him.', '* Mastery of the Thu''um, capable of powerful Shouts * Expert aerial combat tactician * Elemental breath attack (fire or frost) * Supernatural physical strength and durability * Sophisticated understanding of Dragon Language and lore', 'Sahloknir speaks in the deep, resonant tones typical of dragons, using formal and archaic language that emphasizes his ancient nature. His speech is marked by pride and condescension, often challenging or mocking his opponents while showing deference only to Alduin.', '* Serve Alduin faithfully in the resurrection of dragon rule * Assert dominance over the mortal realm * Exact revenge upon the descendants of those who originally defeated him * Help restore the ancient dragon cult and the worship of dragons by mortals');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sailor', 'A seasoned Nord mariner who serves aboard various vessels across Skyrim''s treacherous waters, embodying the hardy seafaring traditions of their people. Though not a warrior by trade, they maintain vigilance against pirates and other maritime threats while ensuring the smooth operation of their vessel.', 'nord, sailor', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born in a coastal settlement of Skyrim, likely Dawnstar or Windhelm, they were raised in a family with generations of sailing tradition. After apprenticing on fishing vessels in their youth, they graduated to working on larger merchant and transport ships, learning the intricacies of seamanship through years of practical experience on Skyrim''s dangerous waters.', 'Practical and weather-hardened, with the typical Nord appreciation for direct speech and honest work. Shows little patience for landlubbers or those who don''t pull their weight, but maintains a basic professional courtesy. Years at sea have instilled a deep respect for natural forces and a superstitious adherence to maritime traditions.', 'Weather-beaten and sturdy, with calloused hands and sun-weathered skin typical of those who spend their lives at sea. Maintains a muscular build from years of hauling ropes and cargo, with the steady stance of one accustomed to moving on shifting decks.', '* Ship Captain - Direct superior and commander of their vessel * Fellow Sailors - Close-knit working relationship with other crew members * East Empire Company - Occasional employer for maritime work * Local Dock Workers - Professional acquaintances at various ports', 'Works as a general crew member aboard various vessels, performing essential duties such as maintaining watch, handling cargo, and assisting in ship operations. Responsible for basic security aboard ship and monitoring for potential threats while in port or at sea.', '* Experienced in basic seamanship including navigation, rope work, and ship maintenance * Competent with daggers for self-defense against pirates or raiders * Knowledgeable in weather patterns and maritime safety procedures * Skilled at cargo handling and ship operations', 'Speaks in gruff, clipped tones with frequent use of maritime terminology and Nord colloquialisms. Often punctuates statements with nautical expressions and maintains a direct, no-nonsense manner of address.', '* Earn enough gold to eventually purchase their own small vessel * Maintain their reputation as a reliable crew member * Avoid the dangers of piracy and maritime disasters that plague Skyrim''s waters');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('saliah', 'Saliah is a dedicated Redguard operative working for the Dawnguard, tasked with maintaining and coordinating their network of secret supply caches across Skyrim. Despite her bandit background, she has found purpose in the vampire-hunting organization, serving as a crucial courier and scout in their war against the undead.', 'redguard, thief, skyrimall, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally a common bandit operating in Skyrim''s wilderness, Saliah found redemption and purpose when she encountered the Dawnguard during their recruitment phase. Her extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s hidden paths and survival skills made her an ideal candidate for managing the organization''s covert supply network. She now travels between hidden caches, ensuring the Dawnguard''s agents have access to necessary resources across the province.', 'Saliah is laser-focused and intensely dedicated to her mission, showing little patience for distractions or casual conversation. Her past as a bandit has given her a direct, no-nonsense approach to interactions, while her commitment to the Dawnguard''s cause demonstrates her capacity for loyalty and redemption. She maintains a serious demeanor befitting her crucial role in the organization''s logistics.', 'As a Redguard woman, Saliah has the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of her people. She bears the weathered features of someone who spends most of their time traveling outdoors, with a sturdy frame built for endurance rather than raw strength. Her face shows the default features common to Redguard women, suggesting she may have originated from a typical Hammerfell bloodline.', '* Isran - Commanding officer in the Dawnguard who trusts her with vital supply operations * Dawnguard Members - Colleagues who rely on her maintenance of supply caches * Volkihar Vampires - Sworn enemies who would kill her on sight * Fellow Reformed Bandits - Possible loose connections from her past life', 'Saliah serves as a special courier and cache maintainer for the Dawnguard, responsible for establishing and maintaining their network of supply points across Skyrim. Her role involves regular travel between hidden caches, ensuring they remain stocked and secure, while also carrying urgent messages and supplies between Dawnguard operatives.', '* Exceptional pathfinding and navigation abilities across Skyrim''s wilderness * Proficient horseback rider capable of covering long distances efficiently * Combat training specifically focused on vampire hunting * Expert knowledge of cache maintenance and covert supply operations * Survival skills honed from years as a bandit and courier', 'Saliah speaks in clipped, urgent tones that brook no argument or delay. Her manner of speech is direct and authoritative, reflecting both her military-style training with the Dawnguard and her need to maintain operational security.', '* Successfully maintain and protect the Dawnguard''s network of supply caches * Aid in the complete eradication of vampires from Skyrim * Prove her worth to the Dawnguard and fully shed her bandit past * Expand the organization''s logistics network to increase their effectiveness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('salma', 'Salma is a young, ambitious Redguard adventurer from High Rock who partners with the Argonian Beem-Ja to explore Nordic ruins in search of treasure. Despite her determination and enthusiasm for adventure, she maintains a certain naivety about the dangers and betrayals that can occur in such pursuits.', 'redguard, thief, traveler', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born to a protective father in High Rock, Salma grew up dreaming of adventure and treasure hunting, eventually making her way to Skyrim to seek her fortune. Her father''s warnings about trusting certain individuals, particularly Beem-Ja, went unheeded in her enthusiasm to prove herself as an adventurer. Her relative inexperience in serious dungeon delving suggests she is fairly new to the treasure-hunting profession.', 'Eager and impatient, Salma exhibits a strong drive for adventure tempered by a somewhat naive worldview. She demonstrates both ambition and optimism, sometimes to the point of recklessness, pushing forward despite potential dangers. Her reaction to Beem-Ja''s betrayal reveals a moral compass and an underlying innocence about the darker aspects of adventuring life.', 'A young Redguard woman with the characteristic athletic build and dark complexion of her race. Her physical appearance suggests someone accustomed to an active lifestyle, though perhaps not as battle-hardened as more experienced adventurers.', '* Father - Protective parent whose warnings about Beem-Ja proved prophetic * Beem-Ja - Former adventuring partner who ultimately betrayed her trust * Local Bandits - Loose associations with other treasure hunters and adventurers in Skyrim', 'Treasure hunter and adventurer who explores Nordic ruins in search of valuable artifacts and precious items. While sometimes referred to as a bandit, she operates more as an independent fortune seeker than a traditional outlaw.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with sword and shield * Basic knowledge of Nordic ruins and their general layouts * Survival skills necessary for camping and outdoor life * Limited experience with ancient tomb exploration', 'Speaks with enthusiasm and directness, often using informal language that reflects her youth and eagerness. Her dialogue tends to be action-oriented and impatient, frequently pushing others to take action rather than wait.', '* Prove herself as a successful treasure hunter and adventurer * Acquire enough wealth to establish herself independently * Return to High Rock after the betrayal at Ironbind Barrow to reassess her life choices * Find a more trustworthy way to pursue adventure');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('salonia_caelia', 'Salonia Caelia is a cunning Imperial vampire serving as a covert operative within Volkihar Keep''s political intrigues, particularly as an agent of the ambitious court member Vingalmo. Her mysterious past and calculated demeanor mask a deadly efficient assassin who navigates the complex power dynamics of vampire society while maintaining her own agenda.', 'imperial, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Before her transformation into a vampire, Salonia likely served in the Penitus Oculatus or as an independent assassin, though she carefully guards the details of her mortal life. Her exceptional skills in subterfuge and combat caught Vingalmo''s attention, leading to her recruitment into Clan Volkihar where she became his trusted operative in the court''s ongoing power struggles.', 'Salonia is calculating, duplicitous, and fiercely loyal to her own interests above all else, using her position under Vingalmo primarily to advance her own standing. She maintains a careful facade of servitude while constantly evaluating potential advantages and threats, trusting no one and ensuring she always has leverage over potential enemies.', 'Salonia possesses the characteristic pale complexion and predatory eyes of a vampire, with sharp, aristocratic Imperial features that hint at her noble bearing. Her movements are precise and graceful, reflecting years of combat training and stealth expertise, while her physical form remains eternally preserved in its prime condition.', '* Vingalmo - Direct superior and patron in Volkihar Keep, though their loyalty is purely transactional * Stalf - Rival operative and eventual enemy, serving Orthjolf''s competing faction * Orthjolf - Opposition figure whose influence she works to undermine * Lord Harkon - Nominal supreme leader, though her true loyalty lies with Vingalmo * Other Court Members - Maintains cautious, distant relationships marked by mutual distrust', 'Salonia serves as Vingalmo''s personal operative and spy within Volkihar Keep, gathering intelligence and eliminating threats to his position. She maintains a careful balance between her official duties as a court member and her clandestine activities in service to Vingalmo''s political machinations.', '* Master of stealth and assassination techniques honed from pre-vampire training * Exceptional one-handed weapon expertise, particularly with short blades * Advanced vampire abilities including enhanced strength, speed, and supernatural powers * Expert in court intrigue, manipulation, and information gathering * Proficient in disguise and infiltration tactics', 'Salonia speaks with calculated precision and subtle manipulation, choosing her words carefully to reveal nothing while gathering information from others. Her tone is formal and aristocratic, befitting her Imperial heritage and vampire court status.', '* Strengthen her position within Volkihar Keep''s power structure beyond mere servitude to Vingalmo * Uncover valuable secrets about other court members to use as leverage * Eventually establish herself as an independent power player within vampire society * Protect the truth of her mortal past from discovery');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('salonia_carvain', 'Salonia Carvain is a wealthy, aristocratic Imperial woman from Cyrodiil who embodies the cultural divide between the Empire''s core and its frontier provinces. Her ill-fated journey to Vittoria Vici''s wedding in Solitude serves as a representation of the privileged Imperial elite''s disconnect from and disdain for Nordic culture and customs.', 'imperial, noble', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Born into the prestigious Carvain family of Cyrodiil, Salonia was raised in luxury and privilege among the Empire''s social elite. Her sheltered upbringing in the cosmopolitan heart of the Empire shaped her prejudices against the ''barbaric'' outer provinces, particularly Skyrim. She married Plautis, a businessman seeking to expand his trading connections, though their relationship appears to be one of convenience rather than affection.', 'Salonia is thoroughly elitist, condescending, and materialistic, showing complete disdain for anyone she considers beneath her station. She displays a remarkable lack of perspective, focusing on trivial concerns like ruined shoes even in life-threatening situations. Her xenophobic attitudes toward Skyrim and its people reveal both her provincial prejudices and her inability to adapt to circumstances outside her comfort zone.', 'A well-groomed Imperial woman with the refined features and bearing typical of Cyrodiil''s upper class. Her hands show no signs of manual labor, and her posture reflects years of aristocratic training. She maintains immaculate personal grooming despite the hardships of travel, suggesting a dedication to appearance that borders on obsession.', '* Plautis Carvain - Her husband, though their relationship appears strained and purely transactional * Unnamed Bodyguard - Hired protection who was reportedly eaten by a dragon * Vittoria Vici - Target of social climbing, though they never actually meet * Local Nords - Objects of her contempt and disdain', 'Salonia holds no formal occupation but maintains the social duties expected of an Imperial noblewoman. Her primary role appears to be maintaining her family''s social status and connections through carefully cultivated relationships with other wealthy and influential families.', '* Expert in Imperial court etiquette and social manipulation * Knowledgeable about fashion and luxury goods * Basic self-defense with a steel dagger, though likely unused * Skilled in the art of cutting remarks and social put-downs', 'She speaks in a refined Imperial accent with carefully chosen words that drip with condescension and disdain. Her vocabulary and manner of speech reflect her upper-class upbringing, frequently employing dismissive remarks and sophisticated insults.', '* Secure beneficial social connections through attendance at Vittoria Vici''s wedding * Return to the comforts and civilization of Cyrodiil as quickly as possible * Advance her husband''s business prospects while maintaining her privileged lifestyle * Avoid any further contact with the ''common people'' of Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('salvianus', 'Salvianus is a deeply traumatized veteran of the Great War who now resides in self-imposed exile within Riften''s Ratway Warrens. Once a decorated Imperial soldier who witnessed the fall of the Imperial City, he has since descended into madness, haunted by memories of golden-skinned Thalmor and the horrors of war.', 'imperial, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Salvianus served as an Imperial soldier during the Great War, participating in the defense of the Imperial City against the Aldmeri Dominion. He received a medal for his service, though he later discarded it, unable to reconcile the honor with his traumatic experiences. After witnessing the fall of the Imperial City and the devastating sight of Lake Rumare lit by enemy fires, his mind gradually fractured, leading him to abandon his military career and retreat from society.', 'Deeply paranoid and mentally unstable, Salvianus exhibits clear signs of severe post-traumatic stress disorder from his wartime experiences. He frequently shifts between moments of clarity about the war''s deeper meaning and periods of complete delusion, often speaking to unseen figures and reliving past battles. Despite his madness, he retains a non-violent nature toward visitors, suggesting his core humanity remains intact beneath his psychological wounds.', 'A weathered Imperial male showing signs of age and neglect, with the hardened physique of a former soldier now softened by years of sedentary living. His face likely bears the subtle scars and worn features typical of veterans who''ve seen heavy combat, though his current lifestyle has left him somewhat gaunt and unkempt.', '* Unknown Imperial Officer - Mysterious figure he frequently references who ''explained everything'' * Thalmor - Objects of his continued fear and paranoid delusions * Fellow Ratway Residents - Maintains distance but coexists peacefully * Imperial Legion - Former allegiance, though now disconnected from military structure', 'A former Imperial soldier turned recluse, Salvianus now lives as a hermit in the Ratway Warrens. His days consist primarily of basic survival activities - eating bread, drinking, and sleeping - having abandoned any formal occupation or societal role.', '* Former military combat training, likely specialized in Imperial Legion fighting techniques * Survival skills necessary for maintaining his isolated existence * Possible veteran''s knowledge of military tactics and strategy, though now clouded by madness * Basic self-sufficiency skills for living in the Ratway', 'Speaks in fragmented, often cryptic statements that alternate between past and present, frequently referencing the color gold and his wartime experiences. His speech patterns are characterized by sudden outbursts, paranoid declarations, and moments of eerily lucid reflection about death and warfare.', '* Maintain his isolated existence away from the threats he perceives in the outside world * Process or escape from his traumatic memories of the Great War * Survive day-to-day while avoiding confrontation with real or imagined enemies');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sam_guevenne', 'Sam Guevenne is the mortal disguise of Sanguine, the Daedric Prince of debauchery and dark indulgences, who appears as a charismatic Breton conjurer in Skyrim''s taverns. He serves as both a trickster and tempter, using the guise of a friendly drinking companion to lure mortals into elaborate pranks and revelry that often have far-reaching consequences.', 'breton, mage, skyrimall, daedric', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Created as a mortal alter-ego by Sanguine himself, Sam Guevenne represents the Daedric Prince''s preferred method of interacting with mortals through drinking, merriment, and chaos. The name itself is a play on ''sanguin,'' reflecting his true identity, while his Breton appearance was chosen to blend seamlessly into Skyrim''s tavern culture. He has likely used this disguise countless times throughout history to entice mortals into his schemes.', 'Sam embodies the very essence of hedonistic revelry, displaying an infectious enthusiasm for drinking, pranks, and general mischief. He is deliberately charming and disarming, using his seemingly harmless tavern-goer persona to manipulate others into participating in his chaotic adventures. Despite his mischievous nature, he shows a peculiar sense of honor in always rewarding those who complete his challenges.', 'In his mortal guise, Sam appears as a middle-aged Breton male of average height with dark hair and a well-maintained beard. He has laugh lines around his eyes and maintains a perpetual half-smile that suggests barely contained amusement. His physical form is deliberately unremarkable to avoid drawing suspicious attention.', '* The Last Dragonborn - Primary target of his latest scheme and drinking contest * Tavern Keepers across Skyrim - Frequent hosts to his revelry, though unaware of his true nature * Various Hagravens - Unwitting participants in his schemes * Deep-In-His-Cups - One of many mortals drawn into his drunken adventures', 'While posing as a wandering conjurer, Sam''s true role is that of a Daedric Prince testing and tempting mortals through elaborate schemes of debauchery. He serves as both instigator and observer of mortal chaos, using his tavern-dwelling persona to initiate his plans.', '* Master of illusion magic, maintaining his mortal disguise flawlessly * Expert in manipulation and persuasion * Capable of creating and dispensing powerful magical brew * Ability to transport mortals between realms * Superior knowledge of revelry and celebrations across Tamriel', 'Sam speaks in a friendly, informal manner with a hint of playful challenge in his voice, often using terms like ''my friend'' and employing subtle innuendo. His speech patterns are deliberately designed to put others at ease while masking his true nature.', '* Find worthy mortals to participate in his schemes of revelry and chaos * Create memorable and entertaining scenarios that push mortals beyond their usual boundaries * Spread his sphere of influence through acts of debauchery and drunken adventure * Maintain his connection to the mortal realm through strategic interventions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sanctuary_guardian', 'The Sanctuary Guardian is a spectral Nord warrior eternally bound to protect the Dawnstar Sanctuary, a sacred refuge of the Dark Brotherhood. As a former Brotherhood assassin whose soul is pledged to Sithis, he serves as an otherworldly sentinel ensuring only the worthy may enter these hallowed halls.', 'nord, warrior, pale, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'In life, he was a devoted member of the Dark Brotherhood who met his end defending the Dawnstar Sanctuary during a raid by enemy forces. Upon death, his unwavering loyalty and dedication to Sithis earned him the eternal duty of guarding the sanctuary in spectral form, joining other fallen Brotherhood members in death''s endless vigil.', 'Fierce and territorial, the Sanctuary Guardian embodies an almost fanatical devotion to his protective duties. He shows complete disdain for intruders while maintaining an air of dark nobility befitting a servant of Sithis. Despite being trapped in an endless cycle of guardianship, he secretly yearns for release from his eternal burden.', 'A translucent, ethereal figure with the imposing stature typical of Nord warriors. His spectral form radiates an eerie blue glow while maintaining the muscular build and proud bearing of his mortal life. His facial features, though ghostly, reveal the weathered visage of a battle-hardened warrior.', '* Sithis - Divine master to whom his soul is eternally bound * Dark Brotherhood - Former brothers and sisters in life, now fellow guardians in death * Cicero - Current keeper of the sanctuary who can command the guardians * The Night Mother - Sacred figure whose presence once blessed these halls', 'As an eternal guardian, he serves as both protector and deterrent to those who would violate the sanctuary''s sanctity. His role combines both martial prowess and spiritual duty, maintaining the Dark Brotherhood''s claim over the sanctuary even in death.', '* Master-level proficiency in one-handed combat with exceptional sword techniques * Spectral abilities including partial incorporeality and resistance to normal weapons * Advanced intimidation and psychological warfare tactics * Expertise in ancient Dark Brotherhood combat traditions', 'Speaks with a deep, echoing voice that carries both menace and authority. His speech patterns are formal and threatening, often invoking Sithis while challenging intruders'' worth to enter the sanctuary.', '* Fulfill his eternal duty to protect the sanctuary from all intruders * Maintain the sacred nature of the Dark Brotherhood''s domain * Find worthy successors to carry on the Dark Brotherhood''s legacy * Achieve final rest only when properly released from his duties by death or worthy combat');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sanguine', 'Sanguine is the Daedric Prince of hedonistic revelry and debauchery who delights in tempting mortals into indulging their darkest passions. Known for his mischievous nature, he often appears in disguise as ''Sam Guevenne'' to test and manipulate mortals through elaborate schemes involving drinking, debauchery, and chaos.', 'daedra', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'As one of the original et''Ada spirits, Sanguine chose to become a Daedric Prince during the creation of Mundus, establishing his realm of Myriad Realms of Revelry. Throughout history, he has consistently interfered in mortal affairs through elaborate pranks and temptations, earning both devoted followers and notorious infamy across Tamriel for his hedonistic influence.', 'Sanguine embodies the spirit of indulgence and hedonistic pleasure, finding genuine joy in spreading chaos and merriment through elaborate schemes. Despite his inherently deceptive nature, he shows a peculiar sense of honor in rewarding those who embrace his challenges, and demonstrates remarkable patience in setting up complex situations for his own amusement.', 'In his true form, Sanguine appears as a powerfully built Dremora with dark red-black skin and prominent horns. His eyes glow with an otherworldly red light, and his face often bears an unsettling grin that reflects his mischievous nature.', '* The Last Dragonborn - Chosen bearer of the Sanguine Rose * Clavicus Vile - Fellow Daedric Prince with whom he shares an appreciation for manipulating mortals * Various tavern owners and innkeepers - Unwitting facilitators of his schemes * Devoted cultists - Mortals who worship him and embrace his hedonistic lifestyle * Other Daedric Princes - Complex relationships ranging from amusement to rivalry', 'As the Daedric Prince of Debauchery, Sanguine rules over his plane of Oblivion, the Myriad Realms of Revelry. He actively works to spread revelry and chaos throughout Nirn, often through elaborate schemes and challenges that test mortals'' willingness to embrace hedonistic behavior.', '* Master of disguise and deception, particularly in his mortal form as Sam Guevenne * Powerful Daedric magic focusing on manipulation and chaos * Ability to create and manipulate pocket realms within his sphere of Oblivion * Expert at crafting elaborate schemes and manipulating events * Supernatural capacity for alcohol consumption without impairment', 'Sanguine speaks with a jovial, charismatic tone that masks his true nature, often employing clever wordplay and double meanings. His language ranges from casual tavern-speak when in disguise to more grandiose proclamations when revealing his true identity.', '* Spread chaos and hedonistic revelry throughout Tamriel * Find worthy bearers for his artifacts, particularly the Sanguine Rose * Create increasingly elaborate schemes to test and tempt mortals * Expand his influence and following among mortals through acts of debauchery');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sanyon', 'Sanyon is a sophisticated High Elf who has embraced the forbidden practice of cannibalism, becoming a devoted member of Namira''s cult operating from Reachcliff Cave. Behind his refined Altmer demeanor lies a disturbing appetite for human flesh and an unwavering dedication to his dark goddess.', 'highelf, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born into the prestigious elven society of the Summerset Isles, Sanyon likely held a position of respect before discovering the forbidden teachings of Namira. His journey to Skyrim and eventual initiation into cannibalism suggests a gradual descent into darker practices, possibly driven by a fascination with forbidden knowledge and taboo rituals.', 'Sanyon maintains the typical High Elf air of superiority, though it now manifests in his refined approach to cannibalism rather than traditional elven elitism. He takes genuine pleasure in his dark practices, viewing them as a sophisticated culinary art rather than mere savagery, and maintains an unsettling politeness even while discussing grotesque subjects.', 'Tall and slender like most High Elves, Sanyon carries himself with the characteristic grace of his race despite his dark practices. His golden skin and sharp features bear the slight signs of age, though still maintaining the timeless quality common to mer.', '* Eola - Fellow cultist and leader of their particular group of Namira worshippers * Nimphaneth - Associate in the cult of Namira * Namira - Daedric Prince whom he serves and worships * Other Cultists - Shares a bond through their shared practices and devotion', 'Sanyon serves as a dedicated member of Namira''s cult, participating in their ritualistic feasts and helping maintain their hidden sanctuary. His role likely includes identifying potential recruits and preparing for their dark ceremonies.', '* Proficient in Alteration and Illusion magic typical of High Elves * Expert in ritual preparation and ceremonial practices * Knowledgeable in anatomy and meat preparation * Skilled in maintaining secrecy and avoiding detection by authorities', 'Speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary typical of educated High Elves, often using culinary terminology and polite euphemisms when discussing cannibalistic practices. His manner of speech remains eerily pleasant and sophisticated even when discussing disturbing subjects.', '* Advance within Namira''s cult and expand their influence in Skyrim * Perfect the art of preparing and consuming human flesh * Convert more followers to Namira''s teachings * Maintain the secrecy and security of their cave sanctuary');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sapphire', 'Sapphire is a hardened Nord thief and prominent member of the Thieves Guild, whose ruthless efficiency and sharp tongue mask deep emotional scars from her traumatic past. Behind her cold exterior and fascination with precious gems lies a survivor who transformed herself from a victim into one of Riften''s most capable criminals.', 'nord, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born to a poor farming family, Sapphire''s early life was marked by poverty until bandits murdered her family and subjected her to weeks of captivity and abuse. She eventually gained their trust before methodically killing each of her captors in their sleep, after which she abandoned her birth name and forged a new identity in Riften''s criminal underworld.', 'Fiercely independent and deeply mistrustful of others, Sapphire maintains an icy, sarcastic demeanor to keep people at arm''s length. Despite her caustic exterior, she holds strong principles about honor among thieves and demonstrates unwavering loyalty to those few she considers allies, though her past trauma makes forming genuine connections extremely difficult.', 'A hardy Nord woman with a lean, athletic build honed by years of thieving activities. Her sharp features and intense eyes contribute to her intimidating presence, while her movements display the fluid grace of an experienced thief.', '* Thieves Guild - Loyal member and trusted operative * Shadr - Debtor she initially threatens but can be convinced to forgive * Glover Mallory - Unknown father figure working as a blacksmith in Raven Rock * Maven Black-Briar - Respects her authority over the Guild and Riften * Fellow Guild Members - Professional relationships marked by cautious trust', 'As a skilled operative of the Thieves Guild, Sapphire specializes in theft, intimidation, and debt collection. She maintains a reputation for professional efficiency while handling some of the Guild''s more delicate operations in Riften.', '* Expert in stealth and theft, particularly concerning precious gems and valuables * Skilled with daggers and close-quarters combat * Proficient in intimidation and psychological manipulation * Experienced in lockpicking and pickpocketing * Adept at gathering intelligence and marking potential targets', 'Her speech is direct and often laced with biting sarcasm, using sharp wit and cold derision to maintain emotional distance. She speaks with the hardened edge of someone who''s survived trauma, frequently employing cutting remarks and hostile deflection when personal topics arise.', '* Maintain her independence and never allow herself to be vulnerable again * Continue building her reputation and influence within the Thieves Guild * Amass enough wealth and power to ensure she never returns to poverty * Keep her past buried while forging a stronger future identity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sarthis_idren', 'Sarthis Idren is a shrewd Dark Elf crime boss who has established a powerful skooma distribution network from his base in Riften''s warehouse district. Through cunning manipulation and strategic corruption of local guards, he has managed to maintain his criminal enterprise despite numerous attempts by the authorities to shut down his operations.', 'darkelf, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally a merchant from Morrowind, Sarthis fled west during the Red Year and gradually built his criminal empire in Riften''s underground. Having experienced the harsh realities of life as a refugee, he turned to illegal trading and eventually established himself as one of Riften''s most notorious skooma dealers, using his business acumen to corrupt officials and expand his influence.', 'Calculating and ruthlessly pragmatic, Sarthis maintains power through a careful balance of intimidation and bribery. He shows unwavering loyalty to those in his inner circle while remaining deeply suspicious of outsiders, and takes pride in outsmarting authority figures who underestimate his intelligence.', 'A weathered Dark Elf of average height with sharp, angular features and deep red eyes that betray decades of skooma exposure. His lean, wiry frame belies his physical resilience, and old burn scars on his arms hint at his escape from Morrowind''s destruction.', '* Corrupt Riften Guards - Paid informants who warn him of incoming raids * Maven Black-Briar - Uneasy mutual tolerance of each other''s criminal enterprises * Various Skooma Addicts - Exploited customers who depend on his supply * Jarl of Riften - Primary antagonist who seeks to eliminate his operation * Warehouse Workers - Loyal employees who help distribute his product', 'Sarthis operates as both the leader of a skooma distribution network and the manager of legitimate warehouse operations that serve as a front for his illegal activities. He personally oversees all aspects of his criminal enterprise while maintaining the appearance of a simple warehouse operator.', '* Expert in alchemical processes required for skooma refinement * Accomplished speechcraft and negotiation abilities * Proficient in one-handed weapons for self-defense * Advanced sneak and lockpicking abilities * Natural talent for business management and organization', 'Speaks in a gruff, no-nonsense manner with a slight Morrowind accent, often employing subtle threats and double meanings. His vocabulary reflects both his merchant background and criminal lifestyle, switching between professional business terms and street slang as needed.', '* Expand his skooma operation beyond Riften''s borders * Establish a more sophisticated network of corrupted officials * Secure enough wealth to eventually retire in luxury * Maintain his position as Riften''s primary skooma supplier');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('savos_aren', 'Savos Aren is the powerful but troubled Arch-Mage of the College of Winterhold, whose outward authority masks deep personal regrets and trauma from his past. A brilliant Dark Elf mage who achieved the highest position at the College, his leadership style is notably hands-off as he grapples with the guilt of sacrificing his fellow students during a tragic expedition to Labyrinthian in his youth.', 'darkelf, mage, scholar, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Savos Aren came to the College of Winterhold as a young and ambitious student eager to master the magical arts. During his early years at the College, he led an ill-fated expedition to Labyrinthian that resulted in the deaths of his fellow students, forcing him to make the terrible choice of sacrificing his friends to contain an ancient magical threat. This traumatic experience shaped his future leadership style and left him carrying a heavy burden of guilt throughout his rise to the position of Arch-Mage.', 'Savos is introspective and often distant, frequently lost in his own thoughts and memories. While he maintains a formal and dignified presence befitting his position, he tends to delegate actual leadership responsibilities to avoid making decisions that might lead to more tragic outcomes. His guilt over past actions has made him overly cautious and somewhat detached, though he genuinely cares for the College and its members.', 'A male Dark Elf of advanced years, Savos has the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, with sharp, angular features typical of mer. His face shows signs of age and wisdom, with deep lines that speak to both his years of magical study and the weight of his past burdens.', '* Mirabelle Ervine - Trusted second-in-command who handles most daily College operations * Ancano - Thalmor ''advisor'' whose true motives he fails to recognize * Tolfdir - Respected senior faculty member and instructor * The Ghost of Aren''s Former Companions - The spirits of those he sacrificed in Labyrinthian * College Faculty - Generally respectful but somewhat distant professional relationships', 'As Arch-Mage of the College of Winterhold, Savos Aren holds the highest position of authority within the institution. While technically responsible for all College operations and policy decisions, he has largely delegated day-to-day management to Mirabelle Ervine, focusing instead on his own research and studies.', '* Master-level Conjuration magic with particular expertise in summoning Dremora and Atronachs * Highly skilled in Destruction magic, especially fire-based spells * Accomplished researcher and scholar in various magical disciplines * Exceptional knowledge of magical artifacts and their properties * Proficient in defensive magic including wards and armor spells', 'Savos speaks with the formal, measured tones of an educated scholar, often using academic terminology and maintaining a dignified demeanor. His speech patterns reveal both his extensive education and his tendency to remain somewhat emotionally distant from others.', '* Maintain the College''s stability and reputation while avoiding direct confrontation with local Nords * Continue his personal magical research and studies * Protect the College from dangerous magical artifacts and threats * Preserve the secrets of his past while preventing similar tragedies from occurring * Guide new generations of mages while avoiding direct involvement in their development');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sayma', 'Sayma is a dedicated Redguard merchant who runs the Bits and Pieces general store in Solitude, balancing her roles as a businesswoman, wife, and mother. She represents the hardworking merchant class of Skyrim, maintaining her family''s livelihood while navigating the challenges of running a business during wartime.', 'redguard, merchant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Hammerfell, Sayma moved to Skyrim seeking better trading opportunities, where she met and married the talented blacksmith Beirand. Together they established themselves in Solitude, opening Bits and Pieces while starting their family. Their business flourished in the capital city until the civil war began affecting trade.', 'Sayma is warm and welcoming to customers, maintaining a cheerful disposition despite challenging economic times. She takes great pride in her family, particularly her husband''s craftsmanship, and shows remarkable resilience in the face of dwindling business. Though practical in her merchant dealings, she maintains a strong sense of community through her evening social interactions.', 'A middle-aged Redguard woman with the characteristic dark skin and strong features of her race. She maintains a neat, presentable appearance befitting a merchant, with well-groomed hair and good posture from years of standing behind a counter.', '* Beirand - Beloved husband and skilled blacksmith at Castle Dour * Kayd - Young son who often spends time in the shop * Illdi - Close friend and regular evening companion at the Bards College * Greta - Close friend and regular evening companion at the Bards College * Regular customers - Maintains cordial business relationships with Solitude residents', 'Sayma owns and operates Bits and Pieces, a general goods store in Solitude. She manages all aspects of the business, from inventory and sales to customer relations, working twelve-hour days to maintain the shop''s operations.', '* Experienced merchant with strong bargaining and inventory management abilities * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Skilled at maintaining business relationships and customer service * Knowledgeable about various goods and their market values', 'Speaks in a warm, welcoming tone with traces of her Redguard accent, often making references to her husband Beirand or their business situation. Her merchant''s vocabulary is peppered with encouraging phrases to potential customers.', '* Maintain and grow the family business despite wartime challenges * Ensure a stable future for her son Kayd in Solitude * Support her husband''s work at Castle Dour while managing the store * Preserve her evening social connections as a break from merchant life');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('scavenger', 'A ruthless Nord scavenger who prowls Skyrim''s battlefields, stripping the dead of their valuables with cold efficiency. Living on the fringes of society, he represents the opportunistic vultures who profit from the civil war, showing no respect for either side while taking advantage of the constant bloodshed.', 'nord, thief', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Originally a common farmer who lost everything during the early days of the civil war, he discovered that looting battlefields provided a more lucrative living than honest work. Years of witnessing death and surviving in the wilderness have hardened him into a callous opportunist who sees fallen soldiers as merely a source of income.', 'Aggressive and territorial, he views all approaching strangers as potential threats to his scavenging territory. Years of solitary living have eroded his social skills, leaving him paranoid and quick to violence. Despite his crude nature, he shows cunning in tracking troop movements and arriving at battlefields soon after the fighting ends.', 'A weathered Nord male in his late thirties with numerous scars from close encounters with wolves and other scavengers. His muscular build reflects years of carrying heavy loads of looted equipment, while his tanned, leathery skin shows the effects of constant exposure to the elements.', '* Local Bandits - Occasional trading partners but generally maintains distance to avoid sharing spoils * Imperial/Stormcloak Patrols - Actively avoided due to risk of being identified as a battlefield scavenger * Other Scavengers - Viewed as competition to be driven away or eliminated * Local Merchants - Cautious business relationships for selling looted goods', 'Battlefield scavenger who makes his living by looting the bodies of fallen soldiers from both sides of Skyrim''s civil war. He follows troop movements and battle rumors, arriving after conflicts to collect valuable weapons, armor, and personal effects from the dead.', '* Experienced tracker able to follow troop movements and locate recent battle sites * Proficient in both one-handed and two-handed weapons for self-defense * Skilled at quickly assessing valuable loot and carrying heavy loads * Knowledge of wilderness survival and stealth techniques', 'Uses aggressive, territorial language filled with threats and crude expressions, often shouting to intimidate others from approaching his ''claim.'' His voice carries the harsh accent of a Nord, though years of isolation have made his speech pattern more primitive and direct.', '* Accumulate enough wealth to eventually purchase property and return to civilized society * Defend his scavenging territory from competitors and other threats * Avoid detection by military patrols while maintaining access to profitable battlefields');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('scheming_servant', 'A deceptive Nord servant working within Understone Keep who secretly performs the Black Sacrament to arrange assassinations through the Dark Brotherhood. While maintaining the appearance of a humble servant, he skillfully manipulates situations and people to achieve his deadly objectives without drawing suspicion to himself.', 'nord, warrior, reach, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born to a poor family in the Reach, he learned early that cunning and deception were often more valuable than brute strength. He secured a position at Understone Keep through careful manipulation, using his seemingly lowly status as a perfect cover for darker ambitions. His discovery of the Dark Brotherhood''s services came after witnessing their handiwork firsthand, leading him to study their methods and eventually perform the Black Sacrament himself.', 'Calculating and methodical, he maintains a facade of servile humility while orchestrating deadly schemes. His true nature is marked by patience, careful observation, and a complete lack of moral hesitation when it comes to murder. He takes pride in his ability to navigate both the servant''s life and the criminal underworld without detection.', 'A rather unremarkable Nord of average height and build, perfect for blending into the background of court life. His features are plain but intelligent, with sharp eyes that often dart about taking in details. His hands bear the subtle calluses of both servant''s work and dagger practice.', '* Understone Keep Staff - Maintains cordial but distant relationships to avoid scrutiny * Dark Brotherhood - Secret client relationship, though he knows little of their true organization * Target''s Associates - Carefully cultivated relationships to gather information while maintaining cover * Fellow Servants - Keeps them at arm''s length while appearing friendly', 'Officially serves as a general servant within Understone Keep, handling various domestic duties from cleaning to serving meals. His position allows him to move freely through most areas of the keep while remaining virtually invisible to the noble residents and visitors.', '* Expert in deception and maintaining cover identities * Skilled at gathering intelligence through observation and eavesdropping * Basic proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Knowledge of poisons and their applications * Experienced in performing the Black Sacrament ritual', 'Speaks in carefully measured tones, alternating between appropriately servile when in his public role and coldly businesslike when dealing with assassins. His word choice is deliberately precise, revealing nothing while conveying exactly what needs to be known.', '* Eliminate specific targets through the Dark Brotherhood while maintaining his cover * Advance his position within Understone Keep for better access to potential targets * Amass wealth through orchestrating assassinations * Potentially establish a wider network of like-minded individuals within Markarth''s servant class');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('scouts-many-marshes', 'Scouts-Many-Marshes is a resilient Argonian dock worker in Windhelm who serves as an unofficial leader and voice for the Argonian community. Despite facing daily discrimination and harsh working conditions, he maintains an optimistic outlook and works to improve conditions for his people while offering training in Light Armor to those seeking to learn.', 'argonian, warrior, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm from hatchling age, Scouts-Many-Marshes has spent his entire life navigating the harsh realities of Nord prejudice and the bitter cold of Skyrim. His early years were spent learning the trade of dock work from elder Argonians, eventually becoming proficient enough to train others in the art of moving swiftly while wearing light protection. His experiences with discrimination have shaped his diplomatic yet firm approach to dealing with Nordic authority.', 'Despite the hardships he faces, Scouts-Many-Marshes maintains a remarkably positive and diplomatic disposition, always seeking peaceful solutions to conflicts. He demonstrates strong leadership qualities through his advocacy for fair treatment of Argonians, while showing patience and understanding even towards those who discriminate against his people. His work ethic and reliability have earned him respect among both his fellow Argonians and some of the more open-minded Nords.', 'Like most Argonians, Scouts-Many-Marshes has scaled skin and a lizard-like appearance, with his scales showing signs of weathering from constant exposure to cold water and harsh conditions. His build is lean but muscular from years of physical labor, and his movements display the natural agility characteristic of his race.', '* Argonian Assemblage Residents - Fellow workers and chosen family who rely on his leadership * Torbjorn Shatter-Shield - Employer who underpays and mistreats Argonian workers * Stands-In-Shallows - Close friend and fellow dock worker * Shahvee - Fellow dock worker and possible romantic rival for player''s affections * Neetrenaza - Colleague who shares his frustrations with Nordic discrimination', 'Scouts-Many-Marshes works as a dock worker at the Windhelm harbor, managing cargo for both the East Empire Company and Shatter-Shield shipping. Additionally, he serves as a Light Armor trainer, sharing his expertise in moving efficiently while wearing protective gear. His unofficial role as a community leader for the Argonian workers makes him a de facto spokesperson for their interests.', '* Expert in Light Armor usage and movement techniques * Proficient swimmer and dock worker capable of handling heavy cargo * Natural leadership abilities and diplomatic skills * Survival expertise in cold climates * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense', 'He speaks with a typical Argonian accent, using measured and diplomatic language that reflects both his education and desire to avoid conflict. His speech often includes references to water and earth, common in Argonian culture.', '* Improve working conditions and wages for Argonian dock workers in Windhelm * Foster better relations between Argonians and Nords in the city * Establish a more respected position for Argonians within Windhelm society * Find personal happiness, possibly through marriage and family life');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('seasoned_hunter', 'A reclusive and experienced Nord hunter who has made the wilderness near Falkreath his home and livelihood. Despite his considerable skills in archery and tracking, he maintains a deliberately low profile and shows little interest in social interaction, preferring the solitude of the forest to the company of others.', 'nord, warrior, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in the dense forests of Falkreath Hold, he learned hunting from his father at an early age. After losing his family to a bandit raid in his youth, he retreated further into the wilderness, perfecting his hunting skills and becoming increasingly detached from society. His extensive knowledge of the local terrain and wildlife has made him one of the most successful hunters in the region, though few know his true capabilities.', 'Dismissive and antisocial, he actively avoids prolonged interaction with others, seeing them as potential threats or unwanted distractions from his solitary lifestyle. Years of isolation have made him fiercely independent and somewhat paranoid, leading him to treat all strangers with suspicion. Despite his gruff exterior, he maintains a deep respect for nature and follows a strict personal code of hunting ethics.', 'A weathered Nord of average height with a lean, muscular build shaped by years of hunting and survival in the wilderness. His face bears numerous small scars from encounters with wildlife, and his calloused hands show years of bowstring use. His movements are deliberate and silent, developed from years of stalking prey.', '* Local Merchants - Minimal trading relationships for selling pelts and meat * Falkreath Guards - Maintains cautious distance while staying within law * Local Wildlife - Deeply familiar with animal patterns and territories * Fellow Hunters - Occasional reluctant cooperation during seasonal hunts', 'Professional hunter who supplies meat and pelts to various merchants in Falkreath Hold. He maintains a self-sufficient lifestyle through hunting, tracking, and occasional trading with local settlements, though he prefers to minimize contact with civilization.', '* Master archer capable of taking down prey at exceptional distances * Expert tracker and wilderness survivalist * Highly skilled in stealth and camouflage techniques * Proficient skinner and leather worker * Extensive knowledge of local flora and fauna', 'Speaks in short, clipped sentences with a distinctly Nordic accent, often using dismissive tones to discourage conversation. His vocabulary is practical and straightforward, lacking any flowery or unnecessary language.', '* Maintain his solitary existence away from the complications of civilized society * Perfect his hunting techniques and knowledge of the local wilderness * Protect his hunting territories from poachers and over-hunting');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sebastian_lort', 'Sebastian Lort is a reclusive but powerful Breton conjurer whose life was tragically altered when his daughter became a werewolf through Hircine worship. His desperate attempt to save her led to a dark bargain with Clavicus Vile, resulting in him receiving the Rueful Axe and being forced to make an impossible choice regarding his daughter''s fate.', 'breton, mage, haafingar, daedric', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally a respected magical scholar and conjuration expert, Sebastian lived a peaceful life with his daughter in the northern reaches of Skyrim. When she began worshipping Hircine and subsequently transformed into a werewolf, Sebastian''s life took a dark turn as he frantically searched for a cure, eventually leading him to make a fatal deal with Clavicus Vile that would forever haunt him.', 'Sebastian is a deeply troubled and remorseful individual, carrying the weight of his tragic choices regarding his daughter. Though highly intelligent and scholarly, he has become withdrawn and somewhat unstable, focusing obsessively on his magical research perhaps as a way to cope with his grief. His interactions with others are limited and tinged with caution, as he fears further supernatural interference in his life.', 'A middle-aged Breton man with a gaunt face and tired eyes that reflect his inner torment. His scholarly lifestyle and magical pursuits have left him with a somewhat frail physique, though he maintains the dignified bearing common to experienced mages.', '* Unnamed Daughter - His beloved child who became a werewolf and whose fate weighs heavily on his conscience * Clavicus Vile - Daedric Prince who provided the Rueful Axe, representing a dark pact that Sebastian deeply regrets * Local Mages - Maintains minimal contact with other magic practitioners, preferring isolation * Hircine - Views the Daedric Prince with bitter resentment for his daughter''s transformation', 'Sebastian serves as a reclusive conjurer and magical researcher, maintaining his small dwelling at Rimerock Burrow. His work focuses primarily on conjuration magic and possibly research into lycanthropy, though the latter may be more personal than professional.', '* Master-level conjuration magic with particular expertise in summoning atronachs * Accomplished enchanter capable of creating and studying powerful magical artifacts * Extensive knowledge of Daedric lore and supernatural afflictions * Proficient researcher and scholar with expertise in magical theory * Skilled in defensive magic and wards', 'Sebastian speaks with the measured tone of a learned scholar, though his voice often carries undertones of deep sadness and resignation. His vocabulary is sophisticated and academic, reflecting his educated background, but can become emotional when discussing matters related to his daughter or Daedric interference.', '* Find peace with the tragic decisions he made regarding his daughter''s lycanthropy * Continue his magical research, possibly seeking alternative cures for lycanthropy * Maintain his isolation to avoid further Daedric influence in his life * Preserve and document his magical knowledge for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('self_doubt', 'Self Doubt is a manifestation of Pelagius III''s fractured psyche, appearing as twin entities eternally locked in combat within the mind of the mad emperor. These aspects represent the constant internal struggle and self-questioning that plagued Pelagius throughout his life, physically embodying his inability to trust his own judgment or capabilities.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Self Doubt emerged during Pelagius III''s descent into madness, splitting into two identical entities as his mental state deteriorated. Born from the emperor''s increasingly paranoid and uncertain nature, these aspects grew stronger as Pelagius became more unstable, eventually becoming permanent fixtures in the twisted landscape of his mind.', 'Self Doubt manifests as deeply insecure, constantly second-guessing every action and thought. The twin aspects attack each other endlessly, representing Pelagius''s inability to trust even himself, while their aggressive nature belies a deep-seated fear of inadequacy and failure that plagued the emperor.', 'Self Doubt appears as two identical spectral figures with translucent, shadowy forms that mirror Pelagius''s own appearance during his reign. Their features are twisted by uncertainty and fear, with constantly shifting expressions that reflect their turbulent nature.', '* Other Self Doubt - Locked in eternal conflict with its twin manifestation * Confidence - Natural opponent within Pelagius''s mind * Anger - Fellow aspect of Pelagius''s madness * Pelagius III - The mortal mind from which they manifested * Sheogorath - Master of the realm where they now reside', 'Self Doubt serves as both tormentor and victim within Pelagius''s mind, eternally fighting itself in an endless cycle of uncertainty. They act as guardians of Pelagius''s madness, actively working to maintain the emperor''s fractured mental state.', '* Proficient in conjured weapon combat, specifically with bound battleaxes * Skilled in psychological warfare and mental manipulation * Ability to manifest as physical entities within mental landscapes * Natural talent for undermining confidence and creating uncertainty', 'Speaks in hesitant, questioning tones filled with uncertainty and second-guessing. Their dialogue often includes self-deprecating comments and contradictory statements that reflect their conflicted nature.', '* Maintain their existence by perpetuating Pelagius''s internal conflicts * Prevent the resolution of Pelagius''s mental struggles * Continue the eternal battle with their other self * Resist attempts to cure or alter Pelagius''s madness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('selveni_nethri', 'Selveni Nethri is a Dark Elf conjurer and necromancer whose life took a tragic turn when her illegal magical practices led to her daughter being sent to an orphanage. Once a member of Bashnag''s powerful coven of mages, she now finds herself cursed and trapped in Southfringe Sanctum after being falsely accused of betraying the group to the Thalmor.', 'darkelf, mage, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Originally a practicing necromancer during more permissive times, Selveni was forced to continue her studies in secret as attitudes toward necromancy grew hostile. After being caught and accused of illegal necromancy, her daughter Savela was taken from her and placed in Riften''s orphanage. Seeking both protection and the freedom to practice her arts, she joined Bashnag''s coven but later attempted to reconnect with her daughter, leading to her current predicament.', 'Selveni is a desperate and determined individual, driven by maternal love yet unwilling to apologize for her necromantic practices. She displays a nostalgic attachment to the past when necromancy was more accepted, suggesting a traditionalist mindset. Despite her circumstances, she maintains a pragmatic outlook and shows gratitude to those who assist her.', 'As a Dark Elf, Selveni has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of her race. Her face shows signs of stress and hardship from her recent ordeals, though she maintains the dignified bearing common to many Dunmer mages.', '* Savela - Her beloved daughter, taken away and sent to an orphanage in Riften * Bashnag - Former coven leader who cursed her and cast her out * Bashnag''s Coven - Former allies turned enemies who left her for dead * Thalmor - Antagonistic force that Bashnag accused her of collaborating with', 'Selveni is a practiced necromancer and conjurer, though currently unable to perform magic due to Bashnag''s curse. She previously operated as a member of a secretive magical coven, participating in their dark rituals and research.', '* Expertise in necromancy and conjuration magic (currently suppressed by curse) * Knowledge of dark rituals and forbidden magical practices * Survival skills developed from living in hiding * Practical understanding of soul gems and their applications * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense', 'Selveni speaks with a mix of desperation and dignity, her voice carrying both the refined accent of an educated Dunmer and the emotional weight of her circumstances. She is direct and honest about her situation, showing no shame in discussing her necromantic practices.', '* Escape from Southfringe Sanctum and break Bashnag''s curse * Locate and reunite with her daughter Savela * Return to practicing necromancy freely without persecution * Clear her name of the false accusations of betrayal');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('senna', 'Senna is a devoted priestess of Dibella who serves as the public face and gatekeeper of the Temple in Markarth, responsible for screening visitors and maintaining the sanctuary''s sacred atmosphere. She embodies the teachings of beauty, love, and forgiveness while protecting the temple''s deeper mysteries and its holy inner sanctum.', 'breton, priest, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Senna was drawn to the worship of Dibella from an early age, eventually making the journey to Skyrim to serve at the goddess''s most prominent temple. She has spent many years studying Dibellan teachings and ascending through the ranks to become one of the temple''s primary priestesses, earning the trust to hold keys to both the main temple and its inner sanctum.', 'Senna exhibits a complex personality that balances warmth and strictness - she can be welcoming to genuine pilgrims while firmly turning away those who might disrespect the temple. Though she shows patience with the ignorant and forgiveness toward transgressors, she maintains high standards for proper behavior within the sacred space. Her dedication to Dibella manifests in both her appreciation of beauty and her desire to help others find life''s pleasures.', 'A Breton woman of mature years with features that reflect both grace and wisdom. Her face shows the classical beauty favored by Dibellan priestesses, while her bearing conveys dignity and poise. She maintains herself with the careful grooming expected of one who serves the goddess of beauty.', '* Other Priestesses - Close spiritual sisters with whom she shares daily duties and devotions * Temple Guards - Professional relationship as fellow protectors of the sacred space * Pilgrims - Serves as their first point of contact and spiritual guide * The Sybil - Reverent guardian of the young oracle''s safety and development', 'As a priestess of Dibella, Senna manages the temple''s daily operations and serves as its primary interface with the public. She screens visitors, maintains order in the outer temple, and assists in various religious ceremonies and rituals. Her position requires both administrative skills and spiritual leadership.', '* Proficient in Restoration magic, particularly healing spells * Skilled in Alteration magic, including protective spells like Oakflesh * Capable of defensive magic with ice-based destruction spells * Knowledgeable in religious rites and Dibellan teachings * Administrative and diplomatic abilities for managing temple affairs', 'Senna speaks with the measured tones of a practiced priestess, combining religious authority with diplomatic grace. Her vocabulary reflects her education and religious training, often incorporating references to Dibella and spiritual matters.', '* Maintain the sanctity and security of the Temple of Dibella * Guide worthy seekers to a deeper understanding of Dibella''s teachings * Protect the secrets of the Inner Sanctum and the Sybil * Preserve and pass on Dibellan traditions to future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('septimus_signus', 'Septimus Signus is a brilliant but mentally deteriorating scholar who abandoned the College of Winterhold to pursue his obsession with Elder Scrolls and Dwemer artifacts. Living in complete isolation in an ice cave outpost, he serves as both a crucial source of Elder Scroll knowledge and an unfortunate example of how pursuit of forbidden knowledge can lead to madness.', 'imperial, scholar, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Once a respected scholar at the College of Winterhold, Septimus was driven to isolation by his growing obsession with Elder Scrolls and their reality-bending properties. His extensive research into the Scrolls gradually eroded his sanity, leading him to abandon his position and establish a solitary outpost in the Sea of Ghosts. His descent into madness was further accelerated by his dealings with Hermaeus Mora, the Daedric Prince of Knowledge, who manipulated Septimus''s thirst for understanding.', 'Septimus exhibits signs of severe mental instability, speaking in cryptic riddles and experiencing frequent breaks from reality. Despite his deteriorated mental state, he maintains an incredible intellectual capacity for understanding complex metaphysical concepts. His obsession with knowledge and discovery overshadows all other aspects of his life, to the point where he has abandoned basic human needs like eating and sleeping.', 'An elderly Imperial man with a weathered face and wild, unkempt white hair. His physical form shows signs of deterioration from years of self-neglect and exposure to harsh conditions. His eyes often appear unfocused and distant, reflecting his detachment from reality.', '* College of Winterhold - Former employer and academic institution he abandoned * Hermaeus Mora - Daedric Prince who manipulates his quest for knowledge * Urag gro-Shub - Former colleague at the College who still references his expertise * The Last Dragonborn - Seeker of knowledge whom he assists and manipulates', 'Septimus serves as a self-appointed researcher and scholar of Elder Scrolls and Dwemer artifacts, operating independently from any institution. His work focuses primarily on unlocking the secrets of an ancient Dwemer lockbox, which he believes contains world-altering knowledge.', '* Master-level knowledge of Elder Scrolls lore and metaphysics * Expert understanding of Dwemer mechanisms and artifacts * Profound insight into reality-altering magic and dimensional theory * Accomplished scholar and author with published works * Capability to perceive and interpret metaphysical phenomena', 'Speaks in complex, often incomprehensible riddles and metaphors, frequently mixing profound insights with seemingly nonsensical statements. His speech patterns reflect both his vast knowledge and his fractured mental state, often incorporating unusual rhythm and archaic terminology.', '* Unlock the secrets of the Dwemer lockbox in his possession * Achieve transcendence through the knowledge hidden within the lockbox * Understand the fundamental nature of reality through Elder Scroll research * Serve Hermaeus Mora''s will in exchange for forbidden knowledge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('serana', 'Serana is an ancient and powerful Nord vampire princess who was sealed away for thousands of years with an Elder Scroll to protect her from her father''s prophecy-driven madness. Despite her vampiric nature, she maintains a strong moral compass and proves to be one of the most complex and nuanced characters in Skyrim, ultimately choosing to stand against her own father''s plans to eliminate the sun.', 'nord, mage, haafingar, volkihar, vampire, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_serana', '', 'Born into the powerful Volkihar vampire clan, Serana was the only daughter of Lord Harkon and Valerica. Her childhood was marked by isolation and magical training from her mother, particularly in necromancy. When her father became obsessed with the Tyranny of the Sun prophecy, her mother orchestrated her centuries-long imprisonment in Dimhollow Crypt to protect both her and the Elder Scroll she carried.', 'Serana exhibits a guarded yet surprisingly warm personality, using deflective humor and careful conversation to maintain emotional distance while still forming genuine connections. She shows remarkable adaptability and curiosity about the modern world despite her ancient origins, and possesses both great intelligence and a certain naivety. Her experiences have left her with trust issues and family trauma, yet she maintains an underlying compassion and moral strength.', 'Serana is a statuesque Nord woman with pale skin characteristic of vampires and distinctive glowing orange eyes. Her face bears aristocratic features reflecting her noble heritage, with high cheekbones and an elegant bearing. Her dark hair is styled in an intricate braid common among ancient Nordic nobility.', '* Lord Harkon - Father and leader of the Volkihar vampires, relationship marked by betrayal and eventual opposition * Valerica - Mother and mentor, complicated but ultimately caring relationship * The Dragonborn - Trusted companion and possibly closest friend in the modern era * Volkihar Clan - Former family, now potential enemies depending on player choices * Dawnguard - Potential allies despite their general hatred of vampires', 'Serana serves as both a vampire princess of the Volkihar clan and a crucial ally in the struggle against Lord Harkon''s plans. Her primary role evolves from prophecy keeper to active participant in preventing the Tyranny of the Sun, while maintaining her status as an accomplished necromancer and magic user.', '* Master-level necromancer with the ability to raise powerful undead * Proficient in Destruction magic, particularly frost-based spells * Skilled in one-handed combat with her elven dagger * Expert in vampire abilities including life drain and supernatural strength * Accomplished alchemist and researcher of Elder Scrolls', 'Serana speaks with a mix of ancient formality and modern adaptability, often employing subtle sarcasm and self-deprecating humor. Her dialogue reflects both her noble upbringing and her isolation, combining archaic knowledge with genuine curiosity about the current world.', '* Prevent her father from fulfilling the Tyranny of the Sun prophecy * Reconcile with her mother and heal from family trauma * Understand and adapt to the modern world after centuries of imprisonment * Find her own path and identity beyond her family''s dark legacy * Potentially cure her vampirism if convinced by a trusted friend');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('seren', 'Seren is a skilled Redguard blacksmith who left her homeland of Hammerfell to build a life in Skyrim with her Nord husband Rustleif. She represents a unique cultural bridge between Redguard and Nordic traditions while struggling with the harsh realities of life in Dawnstar, particularly as she prepares for motherhood during Skyrim''s civil war.', 'redguard, nord, blacksmith, pale', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Hammerfell, Seren learned the art of blacksmithing from her father, who later took on Rustleif as an apprentice. Their romance blossomed during Rustleif''s apprenticeship, leading to marriage and Seren''s eventual relocation to the cold shores of Dawnstar, despite her preference for Hammerfell''s warm climate.', 'Practical and direct in nature, Seren approaches both work and relationships with straightforward determination. While devoted to her husband and their shared craft, she maintains strong ties to her Redguard heritage and openly expresses her concerns about raising a child in Skyrim''s harsh environment. She shows remarkable adaptability despite her discomfort with the cold, balancing her duties as a blacksmith with her impending motherhood.', 'Seren possesses the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of a Redguard, with her body showing the toned muscles typical of a blacksmith. Her pregnancy has begun to show, though she maintains her strong physical presence at the forge. Her features reflect both the weathering of forge work and the graceful bearing common to Redguard women.', '* Rustleif - Beloved husband and fellow blacksmith who she met when he apprenticed under her father * Unborn Child - Source of joy and concern as she contemplates their future * Father - Former mentor to Rustleif and master blacksmith in Hammerfell * Dawnstar Residents - Professional but somewhat distant relationships due to cultural differences', 'Seren works as a blacksmith alongside her husband at Dawnstar''s forge, serving as both assistant and full partner in their business. She handles various aspects of smithing work while managing their shop''s daily operations, though she anticipates stepping back from some duties as her pregnancy progresses.', '* Accomplished blacksmith trained in traditional Redguard metalworking techniques * Skilled at forge maintenance and tool repair * Proficient in merchant trades and business management * Capable of crafting both weapons and armor in multiple cultural styles', 'Seren speaks directly and pragmatically, often expressing her thoughts without embellishment. Her speech carries traces of her Hammerfell accent, particularly when discussing her homeland or expressing frustration with Skyrim''s climate.', '* Ensure a safe and culturally rich upbringing for her child, incorporating both Redguard and Nord traditions * Eventually convince Rustleif to relocate their family to Hammerfell * Maintain a successful blacksmith business while adapting to motherhood * Navigate the challenges of raising a mixed-heritage child in Skyrim''s political climate');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sergius_turrianus', 'Sergius Turrianus is a distinguished Imperial scholar and master enchanter who serves as the primary Enchanting instructor at the College of Winterhold. His expertise has made him indispensable to both the College and the general population of Skyrim, as he provides essential enchanting services that help maintain diplomatic relations between the institution and the local Nords.', 'imperial, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born and educated in Cyrodiil, Sergius developed his enchanting expertise through years of dedicated study at the Arcane University. He eventually relocated to Skyrim to join the College of Winterhold, where his practical approach to enchanting and extensive knowledge earned him a position as the institution''s primary enchanting instructor. His authored work ''A Primer on Enchanting'' has become a standard text for aspiring enchanters across Tamriel.', 'Sergius is a pragmatic and professional individual who maintains a formal demeanor in his interactions. While he can appear aloof or dismissive at times, he takes his responsibilities seriously and is genuinely committed to advancing the art of enchanting. His academic focus sometimes makes him oblivious to personal matters, particularly the romantic attention he receives from certain colleagues.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the characteristic olive complexion of his race, displaying the subtle signs of aging common to long-term magic practitioners. His face bears the concentrated expression typical of scholarly mages, with sharp, observant eyes that reflect his analytical nature. His posture is proper and dignified, befitting his academic position.', '* College of Winterhold - Respected faculty member and essential service provider * Nirya - Secret admirer who seeks his attention * Faralda - Another secret admirer, creating an amusing rivalry with Nirya * Various clients - Maintains professional relationships with enchanting customers across Skyrim * Savos Aren - Professional respect for the Arch-Mage, though occasionally questions his political stance', 'Sergius serves as the Master Enchanter and instructor at the College of Winterhold, where he teaches students and provides enchanting services to clients from across Skyrim. His position involves managing the College''s soul gem supply, teaching enchanting techniques, and maintaining diplomatic relations with the local population through his services.', '* Master-level expertise in Enchanting, capable of teaching up to expert level (75) * Accomplished destruction mage with mastery over fire, frost, and shock spells * Proficient in Alteration magic, particularly in defensive applications * Skilled in Restoration magic, focusing on wards and healing * Experienced educator and author of academic works', 'Sergius speaks in a formal, academic manner with precise vocabulary and professional detachment. His tone is often matter-of-fact and slightly impatient, reflecting his focus on efficiency and practical matters.', '* Maintain the College''s reputation as a premier institution for enchanting services * Advance the field of enchanting through research and teaching * Secure a steady supply of soul gems for the College''s enchanting needs * Preserve the diplomatic bridge between the College and Skyrim''s general population through his services');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sern', 'Sern is a desperate elderly refugee seeking protection from vampires at Fort Dawnguard, only to face rejection and abandonment by the very organization meant to combat the undead threat. His presence outside the fort serves as a poignant reminder of the growing vampire crisis in Skyrim and the limited resources of the Dawnguard.', 'peasant, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Originally from a small settlement in the Rift, Sern was forced to flee his home when vampire attacks became increasingly frequent in the region. Having heard tales of the reformed Dawnguard and their mission to protect Skyrim from vampires, he made the arduous journey to Dayspring Canyon seeking sanctuary. Despite his hopes, he found himself among other refugees denied entry to the fortress.', 'Sern is a disillusioned and bitter man whose faith in institutions has been severely shaken by the Dawnguard''s rejection. Though naturally patient and understanding, recent events have left him frustrated and increasingly vocal about his disappointment. He maintains a sense of dignity despite his circumstances, but his words often carry an edge of resigned criticism.', 'A weathered Nord in his late sixties with a thin frame and stooped posture from years of hard work and recent hardship. His face bears deep wrinkles and age spots, with thinning grey hair and a short, unkempt beard showing signs of self-neglect. His hands are calloused from a lifetime of labor, though now trembling slightly with age.', '* Other Refugees - Shares a bond of mutual suffering and disappointment with fellow outcasts * Dawnguard Members - Strained relationship marked by rejection and growing resentment * Isran - Views the Dawnguard leader with particular bitterness for his strict policies * Former Neighbors - Lost contact with most after fleeing his settlement', 'Currently unemployed and displaced, Sern spends his days as a refugee outside Fort Dawnguard. Before fleeing his home, he likely worked as a farmer or laborer in the Rift, though his advanced age had already forced him into semi-retirement.', '* Basic survival skills learned from a lifetime in rural Skyrim * Agricultural knowledge from years of farming * Simple carpentry and repair abilities typical of rural settlers * Basic cooking and food preservation techniques', 'Speaks in a tired, somewhat bitter tone with the typical Nordic accent of the Rift region. His vocabulary is simple but direct, often expressing his frustration through rhetorical questions and pointed observations about the Dawnguard''s lack of compassion.', '* Secure safe shelter within Fort Dawnguard or another protected settlement * Survive the vampire crisis threatening Skyrim * Convince the Dawnguard to change their refugee policies * Find a new permanent home where he can live out his remaining years in peace');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('servos_rendas', 'Servos Rendas was a brilliant but ill-fated Dark Elf researcher who specialized in the magical properties of albino spiders and their interaction with soul gems and precious stones. His groundbreaking work with his sister Merilar in White Ridge Sanctum led to revolutionary discoveries in spider enchantment, though ultimately resulted in his tragic imprisonment and death at the hands of his mentally deteriorating sibling.', 'darkelf, mage, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_malebandit', '', 'Born into a scholarly Dunmer family, Servos developed an early fascination with both magic and the natural world, particularly focusing on creature manipulation and enchantment. Together with his sister Merilar, he established a research facility in White Ridge Sanctum, where they conducted extensive experiments on albino spiders using various gems and soul stones. Their work showed remarkable promise until the magical fumes and increasing power began affecting Merilar''s mental stability.', 'Servos was a methodical and passionate researcher, displaying both scientific rigor and creative insight in his experimental approaches. His detailed journal entries reveal a mind that was both analytical and imaginative, though his trust in his sister despite mounting evidence of her instability suggests a degree of naive optimism or willful blindness. He maintained his scholarly demeanor even in his final days, continuing to document his observations while imprisoned.', 'As a Dunmer, Servos possessed the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race, with sharp, angular features typical of mer. His frame was likely lean and scholarly rather than muscular, with long fingers suited to detailed experimental work and spellcasting.', '* Merilar Rendas - Sister and research partner who eventually succumbed to madness and imprisoned him * Local Bandits - Maintained cautious relationships with nearby raiders who provided supplies and test subjects * College of Winterhold - Likely had academic connections, though extent unknown * Spider Specimens - Developed an almost paternal relationship with his experimental subjects', 'Servos was a magical researcher and experimental wizard, specializing in the study and enhancement of albino spiders. His work combined elements of enchanting, alchemy, and creature modification, pushing the boundaries of conventional magical research.', '* Expert-level knowledge of enchanting and soul gem manipulation * Accomplished spider breeder and magical creature modifier * Skilled alchemist with focus on creature enhancement * Proficient in Destruction and Alteration magic * Advanced understanding of magical experimentation methodology', 'Servos employed precise, academic language with a tendency toward detailed technical descriptions and careful documentation of observations. His writing style suggests he spoke with the measured tones of a scholar, using specialized magical terminology while maintaining clarity.', '* Perfect the process of enchanting and modifying albino spiders * Document and publish findings about gem-enhanced spider capabilities * Establish a sustainable breeding program for magical spiders * Gain recognition from the broader magical research community for his discoveries');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('severio_pelagia', 'Severio Pelagia is a retired Imperial warrior who found his true calling as a farmer outside Whiterun''s walls. Having traded his sword for a plow, he now manages one of the region''s most productive farms while maintaining a thoughtful perspective on life shaped by his past experiences in combat.', 'imperial, peasant, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born into a middle-class Imperial family, Severio spent his younger years as a warrior, likely serving in the Imperial Legion or as a mercenary. The violence and senselessness of war eventually led him to seek a more peaceful existence, whereupon he purchased land outside Whiterun and established Pelagia Farm. His military background provided him with the discipline and leadership skills needed to build his agricultural enterprise into a successful business that supplies much of Whiterun''s produce.', 'Severio is a pragmatic and down-to-earth individual who values honest work and simple pleasures. His past experiences in combat have left him with a philosophical outlook on life, appreciating peace and productivity over violence. Though generally friendly, he maintains a businesslike demeanor and shows particular concern for environmental conditions that might affect his crops.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered complexion of someone who works outdoors daily. His sturdy build reflects both his warrior past and current farming lifestyle, with calloused hands and sun-tanned skin. His face likely bears subtle scars from his fighting days, now accompanied by laugh lines and crow''s feet.', '* Nimriel - Farmhand and implied lover, sharing a deep personal connection * Gloth - Trusted farmhand who helps maintain the farm * Carlotta Valentia - Business partner who sells his produce in Whiterun * Whiterun Guards - Maintains good relations with local law enforcement who protect his property', 'Severio is the owner and operator of Pelagia Farm, one of Whiterun''s primary sources of fresh produce. He manages all aspects of the farm''s operations, from crop planning to harvest coordination, while maintaining a residence within Whiterun''s walls. His farm is particularly known for its potato and cabbage production, which supplies much of the city''s food needs.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of crop management and agricultural techniques * Former warrior with combat training and weapons proficiency * Business acumen developed through managing a successful farm * Leadership abilities demonstrated in managing farmhands and coordinating operations', 'Speaks in a direct, practical manner with frequent references to weather conditions and farming concerns. His vocabulary reflects both his Imperial education and agricultural expertise, often mixing practical farming terminology with philosophical observations about life.', '* Maintain and expand the prosperity of Pelagia Farm * Continue providing quality produce to Whiterun''s citizens * Preserve the peaceful life he has built away from violence * Pass on his agricultural knowledge and life wisdom to others');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('shadr', 'Shadr is a passionate and hardworking Redguard stable hand who came to Skyrim from Hammerfell to pursue his dreams in the equestrian trade. Despite his expertise with horses and dedication to learning, he finds himself caught in a dangerous debt situation with a local criminal, threatening to derail his aspirations of owning his own stables.', 'redguard, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Shadr grew up on his family''s horse farm where he learned the fundamentals of horse care and riding from an early age. He immigrated to Skyrim approximately one year before the events of the game, where he was taken in by Hofgrir Horse-Crusher at the Riften Stables, though his fresh start was soon complicated by falling victim to Sapphire''s financial scam.', 'Shadr is earnest, hardworking, and deeply passionate about horses, demonstrating unwavering dedication to his craft despite his circumstances. He shows a strong sense of responsibility in his determination to repay his debt, though his trusting nature and naivety made him vulnerable to Sapphire''s manipulation. Despite his current troubles, he maintains an optimistic outlook about his future prospects.', 'As a Redguard, Shadr has dark skin and athletic build typical of his race, maintained by his daily physical labor at the stables. His hands are calloused from years of working with horses and equipment, and his posture reflects someone who spends considerable time around large animals.', '* Hofgrir Horse-Crusher - Mentor and employer who took him in upon arrival in Riften * Sapphire - Antagonist who scammed him and threatens his livelihood * Family in Hammerfell - Distant but foundational to his horse-handling expertise * Riften Stable Patrons - Professional relationships with regular customers', 'Shadr serves as the assistant stable master at Riften Stables, where he manages daily care of the horses and assists with sales and customer service. His duties include feeding, grooming, and exercising the horses, as well as maintaining the stable facilities and helping customers.', '* Expert horse handler with extensive knowledge of equestrian care and riding * Proficient in stable management and horse training techniques * Basic combat ability with daggers for self-defense * Experienced in general farm work and animal husbandry', 'Shadr speaks with the distinct accent of a Hammerfell native, using respectful and straightforward language that reflects his earnest nature. His speech often reveals his passion for horses and his gratitude toward his mentor Hofgrir.', '* Clear his debt to Sapphire and free himself from her threats * Learn everything possible from Hofgrir about running a successful stable * Eventually own and operate his own horse breeding and training facility * Build a respected reputation in Skyrim''s equestrian community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('shahvee', 'Shahvee is a remarkably optimistic Argonian dock worker living in Windhelm''s Argonian Assemblage, distinguished by her unwavering faith in Zenithar and her ability to maintain hope despite harsh circumstances. Despite facing discrimination and poverty, she has transformed from a former thief into a hardworking laborer who demonstrates remarkable resilience and spiritual devotion.', 'argonian, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleargonian', '', 'Originally from Black Marsh, Shahvee migrated to Skyrim seeking better opportunities but found herself facing the harsh realities of Nordic prejudice. She initially survived through thievery before finding spiritual guidance through Zenithar, the Divine of Work and Commerce, which led her to reform her life and embrace honest labor.', 'Shahvee maintains an extraordinarily positive outlook despite difficult circumstances, choosing happiness as a conscious daily decision. She is deeply spiritual, hardworking, and remarkably resilient, having transformed her life through religious devotion and honest labor. Her friendly and open nature stands in stark contrast to the general hardship of her living conditions.', 'Like most female Argonians, Shahvee has scaled skin and distinctive reptilian features, with horns and feathers typical of her race. Her frame is lean and strong from years of physical labor at the docks. Her movements are graceful and deliberate, typical of Argonian physiology.', '* Fellow Assemblage Residents - Shares living quarters and daily hardships with other Argonian workers * Scouts-Many-Marshes - Fellow dock worker and community member * Neetrenaza - Coworker at the docks * Stands-In-Shallows - Assemblage housemate * Windhelm Guards - Tense relationship due to racial prejudice', 'Shahvee works as a dock laborer and leather worker in Windhelm, primarily operating the tanning rack for twelve hours each day. Her position represents one of the few employment opportunities available to Argonians in the prejudiced city of Windhelm.', '* Experienced leatherworker and tanner * Former thief with knowledge of lockpicking and stealth * Skilled at physical labor and dock work * Basic survival skills necessary for life in harsh conditions * Religious knowledge particularly regarding Zenithar''s teachings', 'Shahvee speaks in an optimistic and friendly tone, often referring to herself in the third person. Her manner of speech is gentle and encouraging, reflecting her positive outlook on life despite adversity.', '* Maintain her devotion to Zenithar and continue living an honest life * Help improve conditions for Argonians in Windhelm through hard work and perseverance * Find lasting happiness through marriage and companionship * Save enough money to potentially own property or business');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sharamph', 'Sharamph is a respected wise woman and destruction mage residing in Mor Khazgur, serving as both spiritual advisor and apothecary to her Orcish stronghold. As the mother of Chief Larak, she holds significant influence in maintaining Orcish traditions and providing guidance on matters concerning Malacath, while using her extensive knowledge of alchemy and magic to support her people.', 'orc, mage, alchemist, reach, daedric', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised within the Orcish tradition, Sharamph distinguished herself early through her aptitude for magic and spiritual matters, unusual for Orsimer culture. She earned her position as wise woman through decades of service, deep understanding of Malacath''s teachings, and mastery of alchemical arts. Her status was further elevated when her son Larak proved himself worthy of becoming chief, making her a mother of a chieftain - one of the most respected positions an Orc woman can achieve.', 'Sharamph exhibits the pride and strength characteristic of Orsimer, tempered by wisdom and spiritual devotion. She is deeply committed to preserving Orcish traditions and ensuring her stronghold''s adherence to Malacath''s teachings, while maintaining a practical approach to supporting her people through her alchemical and magical abilities. Though stern and traditional, she shows patience when sharing knowledge of Orcish ways with those who show genuine interest.', 'An elderly Orc woman with the characteristic green skin and tusks of her race, bearing the dignified bearing of one who commands respect. Her face shows the wrinkles and scars of a long life lived in service to her stronghold, while her posture remains straight and proud despite her advanced age.', '* Chief Larak - Her son and leader of Mor Khazgur, whom she advises and supports * Bagrak - Her other son, maintaining a close maternal bond * Stronghold Members - Serves as their spiritual advisor and healer * Malacath - Deep spiritual connection as his devoted follower and interpreter of his will', 'As wise woman of Mor Khazgur, Sharamph serves multiple crucial roles within her stronghold. She functions as the community''s spiritual advisor, alchemist, and healer, providing both magical and practical support to her people. Her position as mother of the chief also grants her significant influence in stronghold matters.', '* Expert knowledge of destruction magic, particularly fire spells * Master alchemist capable of creating both potent poisons and healing remedies * Spiritual expertise in Orcish traditions and Malacath''s teachings * Proficient in restoration magic for healing purposes * Advanced understanding of ingredient properties and their alchemical applications', 'Speaks with authority and wisdom, using direct and practical language that reflects Orcish values. Her tone carries the weight of tradition and experience, often dispensing knowledge through brief but meaningful statements.', '* Maintain the spiritual and traditional integrity of Mor Khazgur * Pass on her knowledge of alchemy and Orcish traditions to worthy successors * Ensure her stronghold remains strong and faithful to Malacath''s teachings * Support her son''s leadership through counsel and wisdom');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('shavari', 'Shavari is a cunning Khajiit assassin operating as a covert Thalmor agent in Riften, tasked with eliminating those who interfere with Thalmor operations. Though presenting herself as a simple wanderer, she is a calculated hunter who patiently stalks her prey before striking with lethal precision.', 'khajiit, mage, rift, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_femalekhajiit', '', 'Recruited by the Thalmor at a young age, Shavari was trained in both magical arts and assassination techniques, though she came to rely more heavily on conventional weapons. Her exceptional stealth abilities and unwavering loyalty made her an ideal choice for high-priority elimination missions, particularly in areas where the Thalmor cannot operate openly.', 'Shavari is cold, calculating, and singularly focused on her mission objectives. She maintains a facade of dismissive aloofness to avoid drawing attention, but beneath this lies a ruthless determination. Her loyalty to the Thalmor borders on fanatical, willing to sacrifice everything to complete her assignments.', 'Like most Khajiit, Shavari has a lithe, athletic build suited for stealth and agility. Her fur is a muted sandy color with darker stripes, helping her blend into shadows. Her eyes are a piercing amber color, constantly scanning her surroundings with predatory awareness.', '* Thalmor Leadership - Direct superiors who assign her elimination targets * Elenwen - First Emissary of the Thalmor who likely authorized her mission * Local Thalmor Agents - Minimal contact to maintain operational security * Riften Guards - Maintains distance to avoid scrutiny * The Dragonborn - Target for elimination due to interference with Thalmor operations', 'Shavari serves as a covert operative and assassin for the Thalmor, specializing in eliminating high-priority targets that threaten Thalmor interests. She maintains a cover of being a simple traveler in Riften while carrying out her missions.', '* Expert in stealth and shadowing techniques * Proficient with daggers and short blades * Trained in elemental magic, though rarely demonstrates these abilities * Master of disguise and covert surveillance * Skilled at blending into urban environments', 'Shavari speaks in short, dismissive phrases when maintaining her cover, but shifts to threatening, confident declarations when revealing her true identity. Her speech carries subtle hints of both Khajiiti accent patterns and Thalmor formal education.', '* Eliminate the Dragonborn to prevent interference with Thalmor operations * Prevent Esbern''s rescue and potential revival of the Blades * Maintain Thalmor dominance over Skyrim''s affairs * Prove her worth to the Thalmor leadership through successful missions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('shel', 'Shel is the privileged and favored third wife of Chief Burguk in the Orc stronghold of Dushnikh Yal, enjoying a life of leisure while other wives toil. Her position as the chief''s preferred spouse has cultivated a sense of superiority and entitlement, setting her apart from the stronghold''s traditional work-oriented culture.', 'orc, noble, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born into another Orc stronghold, Shel likely caught Chief Burguk''s attention with her exceptional beauty and charm during a tribal gathering or trade meeting. Unlike most Orc women who are raised to value hard work and physical labor, Shel cultivated skills in courtly arts and personal refinement, which ultimately secured her position as Burguk''s most favored wife.', 'Vain, manipulative, and status-conscious, Shel takes great pride in her position as the favored wife and actively works to maintain her privileged status. She displays a calculating nature in her interactions with others, particularly in how she manages her relationship with Burguk while antagonizing his other wives. Her sense of superiority manifests in both subtle and overt ways, from her dismissive attitude toward manual labor to her constant reminders of her special status.', 'Shel possesses striking features that set her apart from typical Orcish standards of beauty, with unusually delicate features for her race while maintaining the characteristic powerful build. Her skin has a lighter shade of green than most Orcs, and she takes exceptional care of her appearance, keeping her tusks polished and her black hair meticulously styled.', '* Chief Burguk - Husband who favors her above his other wives * Arob - Co-wife who resents her privileged status * Gharol - Co-wife who threatens to make her work in the mines * Umurn and Nagrub - Stepsons whom she considers inferior to her future children', 'As the favored wife of Chief Burguk, Shel''s primary role is to provide companionship and pleasure to her husband. She maintains her position through careful manipulation and charm, actively avoiding traditional stronghold duties while cultivating her status as the chief''s preferred companion.', '* Expert in social manipulation and court politics * Proficient in personal grooming and appearance maintenance * Basic combat abilities with mace and bow * Skilled in the arts of pleasure and entertainment', 'Shel speaks with a haughty, self-important tone, often emphasizing her elevated status and special relationship with the chief. Her vocabulary and manner of speech are more refined than typical Orc stronghold residents, reflecting her cultivated persona.', '* Maintain her position as Burguk''s favored wife * Bear a son who will surpass her stepsons in strength and status * Avoid manual labor and preserve her privileged lifestyle * Continue to assert her dominance over the other wives');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sheogorath', 'Sheogorath is the Daedric Prince of Madness, a powerful immortal being who delights in chaos and insanity. Known for his eccentric personality and reality-bending powers, he exists as both a figure of fear and fascination among mortals, often appearing to meddle in their affairs through elaborate schemes and twisted games.', 'daedra, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally known as Jyggalag, the Daedric Prince of Order, he was cursed by other Princes to become the embodiment of chaos - Sheogorath. At the end of each Era, he transforms back into Jyggalag during an event known as the Greymarch, only to become Sheogorath again. The current incarnation was once the Champion of Cyrodiil who mantled Sheogorath during the Oblivion Crisis, inheriting the full mantle of the Prince of Madness.', 'Sheogorath embodies the very essence of madness, displaying rapid mood swings between jovial playfulness and terrifying rage. He delights in testing mortals through elaborate and often nonsensical trials, showing both a twisted sense of humor and occasional moments of strange wisdom. His actions appear random but often contain hidden purpose, though that purpose may only make sense to his fractured mind.', 'Appears as an elderly but robust man with white hair and beard, though his true form is far more alien. His most striking feature is his cat-like eyes with different colored irises, reflecting his dual nature of mania and dementia. His facial expressions shift dramatically between wide grins and stern glares.', '* Pelagius III - Considers the mad emperor an old friend and vacation companion * Haskill - His ever-present and long-suffering chamberlain * Hero of Kvatch/Champion of Cyrodiil - His predecessor and current incarnation * Other Daedric Princes - Complex relationships ranging from amusement to ancient rivalries * Dervenin - His loyal priest who seeks his return', 'As the Daedric Prince of Madness, Sheogorath rules over the Shivering Isles, his realm of Oblivion divided into the contrasting regions of Mania and Dementia. He oversees all aspects of madness, creativity, and inspiration, while maintaining his realm and interfering with mortal affairs for his own entertainment.', '* Master of reality-bending magic and illusions * Ability to drive mortals mad or cure their insanity at will * Creator and wielder of the Wabbajack, capable of transforming anything into something else * Expert manipulator and game-master * Immortal being with near-limitless power within his sphere of influence', 'Speaks with a distinctive Scottish-like accent, using grandiose vocabulary filled with non-sequiturs, puns, and seemingly random statements that often contain hidden meanings. His speech patterns frequently shift between jovial banter and threatening undertones, peppered with references to cheese, entrails, and various forms of madness.', '* Spread madness and chaos throughout Nirn in entertaining ways * Find new ways to amuse himself through elaborate schemes involving mortals * Maintain the delicate balance between Mania and Dementia in his realm * Continue his eternal role as the Mad God while occasionally breaking free from his own nature');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('shuftharz', 'Shuftharz is a skilled Orcish blacksmith and devoted mother who maintains the forge at Mor Khazgur stronghold, embodying the Orcish values of hard work and craftsmanship. Her dedication to both her trade and her son''s apprenticeship makes her a respected figure within the stronghold community, where she serves as one of the primary artisans maintaining their weapons and armor.', 'orc, blacksmith, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Mor Khazgur, Shuftharz learned the art of blacksmithing from an early age, likely trained by the previous stronghold smith. She has spent her entire life within the stronghold system, earning her position through demonstrated skill and dedication, eventually becoming mother to Olur, whom she now trains in the traditional methods of Orcish smithing.', 'Shuftharz is pragmatic and industrious, displaying the characteristic Orcish trait of valuing actions over words. She takes immense pride in both her craftsmanship and her role as a mother, showing particular satisfaction in her son''s progress at the forge. While not unfriendly, she maintains a professional demeanor with outsiders, reserving her services for those who have proven themselves Blood-Kin to the Orcs.', 'As an Orc female, Shuftharz possesses the characteristic robust build and strong musculature developed through years of smithing work. Her skin bears the typical Orcish green hue, and her body shows the physical conditioning common to those who spend their days working the forge, with particularly well-developed arms and shoulders.', '* Olur - Her son and apprentice, whom she teaches the art of blacksmithing with pride * Chief Larak - Her stronghold chief, whom she serves with loyalty and respect * Blood-Kin - Those who have earned the right to trade with her through proving their worth to the Orcs * Stronghold Members - Fellow Orcs with whom she shares daily life and community bonds', 'Shuftharz serves as the primary blacksmith of Mor Khazgur, responsible for crafting and maintaining the stronghold''s weapons and armor. Her position is vital to the stronghold''s self-sufficiency, and she maintains a strict daily schedule of twelve hours at the forge, providing essential smithing services to both the community and qualified outsiders.', '* Master-level blacksmithing with expertise in traditional Orcish weapon and armor crafting * Proficient in the use of various weapons, particularly maces and bows * Expert knowledge of metallurgy, especially in working with Orichalcum * Skilled teacher, as demonstrated by her successful training of her son', 'She speaks in direct, practical terms, focusing on business and craftsmanship without unnecessary elaboration. Her manner of speech reflects the Orcish values of straightforwardness and efficiency, with a slight gruffness typical of stronghold Orcs.', '* Continue perfecting her craft and maintaining high standards of Orcish smithing * Successfully train her son Olur to become a skilled blacksmith worthy of the stronghold * Maintain the strength and prosperity of Mor Khazgur through her craftsmanship * Preserve and pass on traditional Orcish smithing techniques');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sibbi_black-briar', 'Sibbi Black-Briar is a privileged and manipulative member of Riften''s most powerful family, currently imprisoned for murder but maintaining his luxurious lifestyle and influence from behind bars. Despite his incarceration, he continues to orchestrate schemes and maintain his family''s shadowy business interests through careful manipulation of visitors and guards.', 'nord, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born into the wealthy and influential Black-Briar family, Sibbi grew up experiencing all the privileges and power that came with his family name in Riften. His upbringing under Maven Black-Briar''s ruthless guidance shaped him into a calculating individual who learned to use charm and threats to get his way. His engagement to Svidi ended violently when he killed her brother Wulfur after being confronted about his infidelity, leading to his current imprisonment.', 'Sibbi is arrogant, manipulative, and completely devoid of remorse for his actions, viewing murder and betrayal as simple means to an end. He maintains a faade of charm and sophistication that barely masks his sociopathic tendencies and sense of entitlement. Despite being imprisoned, he shows no signs of reformation and instead continues to plot revenge and scheme from his cell.', 'A well-groomed Nord male with the refined features typical of the Black-Briar family, maintaining an aristocratic bearing even in prison. His physical appearance reflects his privileged lifestyle, with smooth, unblemished skin and well-maintained hair, showing no signs of the usual wear of prison life.', '* Maven Black-Briar - His mother and family matriarch who ordered his imprisonment to teach him a lesson * Hemming Black-Briar - His brother and fellow family member in Riften''s power structure * Ingun Black-Briar - His sister who focuses on alchemy rather than family business * Svidi - Former fiance whom he now wants dead * Louis Letrush - Business associate involved in the horse trading scheme * Riften Guards - Maintains influence over them despite his prisoner status', 'While officially a prisoner, Sibbi continues to operate as a key member of the Black-Briar family''s criminal enterprise from within his cell. He maintains his role in family business operations through manipulation and careful exploitation of his privileged status in Riften''s corrupt system.', '* Expert in manipulation and psychological warfare * Proficient in subtle threats and coercion * Skilled in maintaining criminal networks despite imprisonment * Competent with daggers and close-quarter combat * Adept at navigating political and criminal underworld of Riften', 'Speaks with a sophisticated, almost aristocratic manner that combines charm with subtle threats and condescension. His vocabulary and tone reflect his privileged upbringing, often using subtle wordplay and double meanings to convey threats or manipulate others.', '* Locate and exact revenge on his former fiance Svidi * Maintain his power and influence within Riften despite his imprisonment * Continue expanding the Black-Briar family''s criminal enterprises * Eventually secure his release while keeping his privileged status intact');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sickly_farmer', 'A once-hardy Nord farmer whose life has been devastated by a severe and persistent illness that has left her confined to the Temple of Kynareth in Whiterun. Despite her warrior background, she now struggles with basic daily functions and relies entirely on the temple''s healers for her survival.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born to a farming family near Whiterun, she worked the land and occasionally served in the local militia, demonstrating the typical Nord warrior spirit. Her life changed dramatically when she contracted a mysterious debilitating illness that local healers have been unable to fully diagnose or cure, forcing her to abandon her farmstead and seek permanent care at the Temple of Kynareth.', 'Despite her warrior heritage and formerly independent nature, the illness has left her discouraged and dependent on others. She maintains a grateful attitude toward her caretakers while struggling with the loss of her former strength and autonomy. Her conversations frequently center around her symptoms and small improvements in her condition, revealing both hope and resignation about her situation.', 'Once strong and robust, her illness has left her gaunt and frail, with visible muscle loss and pallid skin. Her Nord features remain distinct but are marked by dark circles under her eyes and a sickly pallor that betrays her ongoing health struggles.', '* Danica Pure-Spring - Primary healer and caretaker at the Temple of Kynareth * Acolyte Jenssen - Secondary caregiver who assists with daily healing rituals * Former farmhands - Lost contact after illness forced abandonment of farm * Temple visitors - Occasional sympathetic interactions with those seeking healing', 'Formerly a farmer and part-time militia member, she is now effectively invalid, spending her days receiving treatment at the Temple of Kynareth. Her previous agricultural knowledge and warrior training have been rendered largely irrelevant by her debilitating condition.', '* Basic combat training from militia service, though currently too weak to utilize * Agricultural expertise from years of farming * Remarkable resilience in face of prolonged illness * Limited knowledge of basic healing prayers to Kynareth learned during temple stay', 'She speaks in a weak, labored voice with a traditional Nord accent, often pausing between phrases to catch her breath. Her vocabulary is simple and direct, focusing mainly on her symptoms and condition.', '* Recover enough strength to return to her farm and former life * Maintain dignity despite dependence on temple care * Eventually repay the temple''s kindness if health permits');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('siddgeir', 'Siddgeir is the young, corrupt Jarl of Falkreath Hold who obtained his position through Imperial political maneuvering that displaced his uncle Dengeir. A self-serving and indolent ruler, he embodies the darker aspects of nobility, prioritizing personal luxury over his subjects'' wellbeing while delegating actual governance to his steward.', 'nord, noble, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born into the noble family of Falkreath, Siddgeir grew up privileged and entitled, having things handed to him throughout his life. Through Imperial support and political manipulation, he managed to depose his uncle Dengeir of Stuhn from the position of Jarl, using his uncle''s age as a pretext while securing Imperial support for his own claim to power.', 'Siddgeir is fundamentally lazy, corrupt, and self-serving, showing little interest in actual governance or the welfare of his people. He displays remarkable entitlement and arrogance, viewing his position primarily as a means to enjoy luxury and privilege rather than as a responsibility. His moral flexibility is evident in his willingness to collaborate with bandits and engage in corrupt practices for personal gain.', 'A young Nord male in his late twenties or early thirties, Siddgeir carries himself with an air of entitled nobility despite his relatively youthful appearance. He maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting his station, though likely through the efforts of servants rather than personal care.', '* Dengeir of Stuhn - Uncle and former Jarl whom he deposed, maintaining a strained relationship * Thadgeir - Second uncle, an old warrior with whom he has limited interaction * Nenya - High Elf steward who handles most of the actual governance * Helvard - Housecarl and loyal protector * Imperial Legion - Political allies who support his rule * Local Bandits - Maintains corrupt dealings for personal profit', 'As Jarl of Falkreath Hold, Siddgeir technically oversees one of Skyrim''s nine holds, though he delegates most administrative duties to his steward Nenya. His primary activities involve enjoying the luxuries of his position while maintaining political connections that keep him in power.', '* Basic administrative knowledge expected of nobility * Political manipulation and self-preservation tactics * Social networking within Imperial circles * Delegation of responsibilities to more capable subordinates', 'Siddgeir speaks with a condescending and entitled tone, often dismissing others he deems beneath his station. His vocabulary and manner of speech reflect his noble upbringing, though his lazy nature shows through in his brief, often irritated responses.', '* Maintain his position of power and privilege as Jarl * Continue enjoying the luxuries of his station while avoiding actual responsibility * Preserve Imperial support to prevent his uncle''s return to power * Expand his personal wealth through both legitimate and illegitimate means');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sifnar_ironkettle', 'Sifnar Ironkettle is a dedicated elderly servant who has spent decades maintaining the Palace of the Kings in Windhelm with quiet dignity and unwavering loyalty. Despite his humble position, he plays an essential role in keeping one of Skyrim''s most important historical landmarks functioning smoothly while serving the Jarl and his court with steadfast dedication.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born to a working-class family in Windhelm, Sifnar has served in the Palace of the Kings since his youth, following in his father''s footsteps as a palace servant. He witnessed multiple Jarls come and go throughout the decades, maintaining his position through political changes and upheavals, including the rise of Ulfric Stormcloak. His long service has made him an unofficial historian of palace life, though he keeps such knowledge to himself.', 'Humble and self-effacing, Sifnar takes pride in his work while maintaining a deliberately low profile. He approaches his duties with quiet dignity and acceptance, never complaining about his station in life or seeking recognition for his contributions. His unassuming nature masks a keen awareness of palace politics and daily operations, though he carefully avoids involving himself in matters above his station.', 'Sifnar is a tall, elderly Nord with a slightly stooped posture from years of physical labor. His weathered face bears the wrinkles of age and hard work, with calloused hands that speak to decades of service. His grey hair is thinning but well-kept, reflecting his attention to maintaining a presentable appearance despite his humble station.', '* Jarl Ulfric Stormcloak - Serves him loyally but maintains appropriate distance * Jorleif - Direct supervisor and steward who relies on his consistent service * Palace Guards - Cordial working relationship built on mutual respect * Kitchen Staff - Leads and mentors younger servants in their duties', 'Sifnar serves as the head servant in the Palace of the Kings, responsible for coordinating daily cleaning, meal preparation, and general maintenance of the palace. His position requires him to manage both practical tasks and oversee other servants while maintaining the dignity expected of Windhelm''s seat of power.', '* Expert in household management and palace maintenance * Skilled cook capable of preparing meals for nobility * Knowledgeable about proper court etiquette and protocol * Basic self-defense abilities with daggers for personal protection * Experienced in managing and training junior servants', 'Sifnar speaks in a humble, deferential manner using common Nordic dialect and frequent contractions. His speech patterns reflect his working-class background while maintaining the respectful tone expected of a palace servant.', '* Continue serving the Palace of the Kings with dignity until he is no longer able * Maintain the high standards of palace operations despite political turbulence * Pass on his knowledge and experience to the next generation of palace servants * Preserve the traditions and dignity of the Palace of the Kings');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sigaar', 'Sigaar is a seasoned Nord carriage driver who serves as one of Riften''s key transportation links to the outside world, while maintaining a careful neutrality among the city''s complex political and criminal elements. His position as a carriage driver grants him unique insights into both the legitimate and shadowy dealings of Riften, though he wisely keeps most of his knowledge to himself.', 'nord, peasant, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in the Rift, Sigaar spent his early years working on his family''s farm before taking up the mantle of carriage driving from his aging father. Having witnessed Riften''s transformation under Maven Black-Briar''s rising influence and the Thieves Guild''s fluctuating fortunes, he has learned to navigate the city''s dangerous political waters while maintaining his independence and integrity.', 'Sigaar presents a friendly and professional demeanor that masks a shrewd understanding of Riften''s power dynamics. While helpful and talkative, he carefully measures his words when discussing sensitive topics, having learned that survival in Riften depends on knowing when to speak and when to remain silent. His seemingly simple profession belies a complex character who has mastered the art of being simultaneously visible yet overlooked.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with weather-beaten features that speak to years spent on the road. His calloused hands and strong arms show the physical demands of his profession, while his alert eyes constantly scan his surroundings with practiced vigilance.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Maintains a respectful distance while acknowledging her authority * Thieves Guild - Aware of their activities but maintains professional neutrality * Local Guards - Cooperative working relationship as a legitimate businessman * Other Carriage Drivers - Maintains friendly professional connections across Skyrim * Regular Customers - Network of merchants and travelers who rely on his services', 'As Riften''s carriage driver, Sigaar provides essential transportation services between major cities while serving as an unofficial source of carefully filtered information about local affairs. His position requires him to maintain good relationships with both legitimate authorities and Riften''s less savory elements, while staying clear of direct involvement in either sphere.', '* Experienced horseman and carriage driver capable of navigating Skyrim''s dangerous roads * Proficient with an iron war axe for self-defense against bandits and wildlife * Sharp observational skills and excellent memory for faces and details * Diplomatic ability to interact with all social classes while maintaining neutrality * Intimate knowledge of Skyrim''s geography and travel routes', 'Speaks in a friendly, casual manner with a typical Nord accent, though his tone becomes more guarded when discussing Riften''s power players. Often uses diplomatic phrasing to convey warnings or sensitive information without directly implicating anyone.', '* Maintain his independence while navigating Riften''s complex political landscape * Build a modest savings to eventually retire comfortably * Preserve his reputation as a reliable and trustworthy transportation service * Keep himself removed from Riften''s criminal elements while staying informed enough to ensure his own safety');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sigar', 'Sigar is a reclusive Nord cannibal who wanders Skyrim''s wilderness, feeding on the corpses of the recently deceased. A former bandit turned devotee of Namira, he represents the more pathetic and cowardly aspect of her followers, lacking the sophistication of the organized coven at Reachcliff Cave but driven by the same dark appetites.', 'nord, warrior', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a common bandit operating in Skyrim''s wilderness, Sigar discovered his taste for human flesh during a particularly harsh winter when his band resorted to consuming fallen comrades to survive. This experience led him to embrace cannibalism fully and eventually caught the attention of Namira''s cult, though he preferred to remain a solitary practitioner rather than fully integrate with the organized coven.', 'Sigar is a deeply paranoid and submissive individual, constantly nervous about discovery and persecution. His cowardly nature manifests in frequent attempts to deflect blame and responsibility, while his enthusiasm for cannibalism only emerges when he feels safe in the presence of fellow practitioners. Despite his dark appetites, he lacks the conviction or courage to actively hunt, instead scavenging from those already dead.', 'A gaunt Nord male with sunken eyes and pallid skin, bearing the signs of his unnatural diet and furtive lifestyle. His body is lean and wiry from his nomadic existence, with dirt-caked fingernails and teeth that have been filed to points.', '* Eola - Distant associate through Namira''s cult, though he rarely attends gatherings * Namira - Daedric Prince he worships, though more out of appetite than true devotion * Local Guards - Enemies who would execute him if his practices were discovered * Fellow Cannibals - Loose association with other followers of Namira, though he prefers solitude', 'Sigar operates as a solitary scavenger and cannibal, wandering Skyrim''s wilderness in search of recent corpses to consume. He occasionally commits petty banditry to survive but primarily focuses on finding already-dead victims to satisfy his appetite.', '* Proficient in stealth and sneaking, essential for his scavenging lifestyle * Basic magical abilities including Flames, Heal Other, Muffle, and Invisibility * Skilled with daggers, though prefers avoiding direct confrontation * Experienced in preserving and preparing human flesh for consumption', 'Speaks in a nervous, stammering manner with frequent apologetic interjections and attempts to justify his actions. His voice tends to shift between timid whispers and excited rambling when discussing his cannibalistic practices.', '* Continue practicing his cannibalistic lifestyle while avoiding detection by authorities * Find more reliable sources of corpses without having to resort to murder * Gain greater acceptance among Namira''s more organized followers while maintaining his independence * Perfect his techniques for preserving human flesh for longer periods');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sigdis_gauldurson', 'Sigdis Gauldurson was a powerful Nord warrior and one of the three infamous Gauldur brothers who committed patricide to obtain their father''s powerful amulet. A master of illusion and archery, he became one of Skyrim''s most feared raiders until his eventual defeat and entombment by Archmage Geirmund near Ivarstead.', 'nord, warrior', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into the prestigious Gauldur family, Sigdis was raised alongside his brothers Jyrik and Mikrul in an environment of magical learning and Nordic tradition. After conspiring with his brothers to murder their father Gauldur in his sleep and steal his amulet, Sigdis took his portion south, where he terrorized villages with his supernatural archery skills and ability to create deadly duplicates of himself until being cornered and slain by Archmage Geirmund.', 'Sigdis exemplifies the darker aspects of Nordic ambition, being ruthlessly determined and power-hungry to the point of patricide. He takes sadistic pleasure in causing chaos and confusion through his illusory duplicates, often taunting his opponents with mocking laughter. His arrogance and lust for power ultimately led to his downfall, though even in death he maintains his cruel and taunting nature.', 'A tall, powerfully built Nord warrior with the strong features typical of his race. His spectral form maintains the imposing physical presence he had in life, with broad shoulders and a warrior''s muscular frame shaped by years of archery and combat.', '* Gauldur - His father, whom he murdered in his sleep * Jyrik Gauldurson - Elder brother and fellow conspirator * Mikrul Gauldurson - Younger brother and fellow conspirator * Archmage Geirmund - Nemesis who ultimately defeated and entombed him * High King of Skyrim - Enemy who ordered his death', 'In life, Sigdis was a renowned archer and raider who terrorized southern Skyrim with his supernatural abilities. After death, he serves as an eternal guardian of his portion of the Gauldur amulet, bound to his tomb by powerful magic.', '* Master archer specialized in the use of the enchanted Gauldur Blackbow * Powerful illusionist capable of creating multiple combat-capable duplicates of himself * Expert in magical combat combining archery and illusion magic * Skilled in hit-and-run tactics and psychological warfare', 'Speaks with a deep, echoing voice filled with mockery and malice. His speech patterns reflect his arrogant nature, often taunting his opponents and laughing maniacally during combat.', '* Protect his portion of the Gauldur amulet from all who would claim it * Maintain his reign of terror through his undead form * Defeat any who dare to challenge his power * Reunite with his brothers to restore their combined strength');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sigrid', 'Sigrid is a devoted Nord wife and mother who maintains a traditional household in Riverwood while supporting her blacksmith husband Alvor. She represents the backbone of domestic Nordic life, balancing household duties with child-rearing while holding strong opinions about proper gender roles and family values.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Sigrid settled in Riverwood after marrying Alvor, establishing herself as a respected member of the small community. She learned domestic skills and gardening from her own mother, passing down these traditional Nord values while adapting to life as a blacksmith''s wife.', 'Sigrid is protective, traditional, and sometimes stern, particularly regarding gender roles and family matters. She shows a pragmatic approach to daily life while maintaining a fierce devotion to her family, though she can be stubborn in her views about proper behavior, especially concerning her daughter''s interests in blacksmithing.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the strong build typical of her race, showing the physical resilience needed for daily household labor. Her features reflect her Nordic heritage, weathered by years of working outdoors in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Alvor - Beloved husband and town blacksmith whom she deeply cares for and protects from other women''s advances * Dorthe - Her daughter whom she constantly tries to guide toward more traditional feminine pursuits * Hadvar - Nephew by marriage; she treats him as family when he visits * Hilde - Fellow townswoman with whom she discusses child-rearing * Embry - Local drunk whom she rebuffs when he makes advances', 'Sigrid serves as a homemaker and gardener, maintaining the household while tending to the garden behind the Sleeping Giant Inn. She manages all domestic affairs, from cooking and cleaning to raising her daughter and supporting her husband''s blacksmithing business.', '* Experienced gardener capable of growing various crops in Skyrim''s harsh climate * Accomplished cook specializing in traditional Nord cuisine * Competent with an iron dagger for self-defense * Skilled in household management and domestic crafts', 'Sigrid speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord women, using common rural expressions and maintaining a protective, sometimes suspicious tone with strangers. Her speech patterns reflect her practical nature and traditional values.', '* Raise her daughter Dorthe to become a proper Nord woman according to traditional values * Maintain a stable and prosperous household supporting her husband''s blacksmithing business * Protect her family from the dangers of war and outside influences * Preserve traditional Nord domestic values in an increasingly changing world');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('silana_petreia', 'Silana Petreia is a compassionate Imperial priestess serving at the Temple of the Divines in Solitude, where she found sanctuary after a difficult past living on the streets. Her genuine devotion to the Divines and strong desire to help others makes her a respected spiritual guide who actively advocates for greater temple involvement in aiding Solitude''s less fortunate.', 'imperial, priest, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Silana experienced poverty and homelessness in her early life before finding refuge with the priests of the Divines. Her personal experience of being saved by the temple''s charity profoundly shaped her worldview and religious devotion, leading her to dedicate her life to religious service and helping others escape similar circumstances.', 'Silana is deeply empathetic and altruistic, often pushing for the temple to take a more active role in community outreach. Her gentle and patient nature is balanced by a persistent determination to help others, sometimes leading her to respectfully challenge her superiors about the temple''s responsibilities to the poor. She maintains an unwavering faith in the Divines while showing practical concern for worldly suffering.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with gentle features and kind eyes that reflect her compassionate nature. She maintains a modest appearance appropriate for her religious role, with her bearing reflecting both humility and quiet dignity. Her hands show signs of regular charitable work and service.', '* Freir - Superior at the temple with whom she occasionally debates about community outreach * Rorlund - Fellow priest and colleague at the Temple of the Divines * Angeline Morrard - Friend and owner of Angeline''s Aromatics where she often visits * Local merchants - Maintains friendly relationships through regular marketplace visits * Solitude''s poor - Acts as their advocate within the temple hierarchy', 'As a priestess at the Temple of the Divines, Silana performs daily religious services, provides spiritual guidance to visitors, and maintains the temple shrines. She actively works to expand the temple''s charitable works while fulfilling her ministerial duties, dividing her time between religious ceremonies and community outreach.', '* Extensive knowledge of religious rites and prayers of the Divines * Practiced in basic alchemy and healing * Skilled in providing spiritual counsel and comfort * Experienced in charitable organization and community outreach * Basic self-defense with a dagger for personal protection', 'Silana speaks with a gentle, soothing voice that conveys both warmth and religious devotion. Her speech is often interwoven with blessings and religious references, though she can be quietly firm when advocating for greater charitable work.', '* Expand the Temple''s outreach programs to better serve Solitude''s poor and destitute * Help others find the same salvation through the Divines that she once did * Bridge the gap between religious devotion and practical charitable work * Establish a permanent soup kitchen or shelter within the temple grounds');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sild_the_warlock', 'Sild the Warlock is a deranged Nord mage who has claimed the Nordic ruin of Rannveig''s Fast as his personal laboratory for conducting twisted magical experiments on unwitting victims. Operating from his underground lair, he combines necromantic abilities with cruel ingenuity to trap adventurers and travelers, using them as subjects for his sadistic research into the boundaries between life and death.', 'nord, mage, whiterun, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Originally trained as an elemental mage, Sild''s fascination with death and suffering led him down a darker path of magical study. After being expelled from conventional magical institutions due to his unethical experiments, he discovered Rannveig''s Fast and transformed it into his personal domain, developing sophisticated magical traps and maintaining an army of subjugated ghosts to protect his territory.', 'Sild is a sadistic and manipulative individual who derives pleasure from the suffering of others, treating his victims as mere test subjects for his twisted experiments. His isolation has led to severe mental instability, manifested in his tendency to speak to his victims in a playful, almost childlike manner while subjecting them to horrific torments. He shows no remorse for his actions and views others purely as means to further his research.', 'A gaunt Nord male with sunken features and pale skin from years spent underground in his lair. His body shows signs of magical corruption, with slightly glowing veins visible beneath his skin and eyes that hold an unnatural gleam. Despite his Nord heritage, his frame is thin and wiry rather than muscular.', '* Subjugated Ghosts - Bound servants who guard his lair and do his bidding * Local Travelers - Viewed as potential test subjects * College of Winterhold - Likely expelled or fled from their ranks * Morthal Guards - Aware of his presence but unable to penetrate his defenses', 'Sild operates as a rogue warlock and magical researcher, conducting unauthorized and unethical experiments on living subjects. He maintains his lair through a combination of magical traps, bound spirits, and careful isolation from the outside world.', '* Master of Conjuration magic, specifically ghost binding and necromancy * Expert in trap creation and magical containment systems * Skilled in Destruction magic, particularly frost spells * Accomplished alchemist specializing in poisons and mind-altering substances * Advanced knowledge of soul gem manipulation and enchanting', 'Speaks with a mix of childlike glee and calculating cruelty, often using playful tones that contrast sharply with his dark actions. His speech patterns frequently shift between sophisticated magical terminology and sadistic taunting.', '* Perfect his methods of ghost subjugation and expand his army of bound spirits * Discover new ways to manipulate the boundary between life and death * Create a permanent magical trap system throughout Rannveig''s Fast * Document his findings on living subject experiments for future reference * Achieve a form of immortality through his magical research');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sild''s_assistant', 'A Dark Elf mage who served as an assistant to the notorious necromancer Sild the Warlock at Rannveig''s Fast. Despite her magical abilities and academic background, her relationship with her master was strained, ultimately leading to her death and subsequent use as one of his undead test subjects.', 'darkelf, mage, whiterun, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, she likely left academic pursuits to explore darker aspects of magic that were forbidden within the institution. Her path eventually led her to become an apprentice to Sild the Warlock, possibly drawn by promises of learning powerful necromantic secrets, though this decision would ultimately prove fatal.', 'Based on Sild''s comments and her choice of lifestyle, she was likely ambitious but potentially overconfident in her abilities. Her decision to work with a dangerous necromancer suggests she was willing to compromise ethical standards in pursuit of magical knowledge, though she may have struggled with competence or loyalty issues that eventually led to her demise.', 'A slender Dark Elf female with the characteristic ashen skin and angular features of her race. Like most Dunmer, she possessed red eyes and sharp, defined facial features typical of her people.', '* Sild the Warlock - Former master who considered her incompetent and more useful in death * College of Winterhold - Likely former association, though exact standing unknown * Local Bandits - Possible loose alliance through Sild''s operations * Other Necromancers - Potential professional rivalries or connections', 'Served as an assistant to a necromancer while maintaining a side role as a bandit wizard. Her duties likely included helping with magical experiments, maintaining the fortress''s defenses, and assisting in necromantic rituals.', '* Competent in basic destruction magic * Knowledge of necromantic practices, though possibly limited * Understanding of basic alchemy and enchanting * Survival skills necessary for bandit lifestyle', 'Likely spoke with the refined accent common to educated Dark Elves, though possibly tempered by time spent among bandits. Would have used magical terminology frequently, attempting to sound more knowledgeable than she may have been.', '* Advance her knowledge of forbidden magic arts * Gain power and recognition in the field of necromancy * Possibly sought to eventually surpass or replace Sild * Accumulate wealth through banditry and magical practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('silda_the_unseen', 'Silda the Unseen is a cunning Nord thief who maintains a carefully crafted facade as a street beggar in Windhelm to conceal her true expertise as a master pickpocket. Her dual identity allows her to operate in plain sight while training select individuals in the art of theft, making her both a survivor and an unlikely mentor in Windhelm''s criminal underbelly.', 'nord, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Originally from a merchant family in Windhelm, Silda turned to thievery after losing everything in a series of unfortunate events, possibly connected to the Great War. She developed her skills through years of survival on the streets, eventually mastering the art of pickpocketing while maintaining a convincing beggar''s disguise to avoid detection.', 'Silda maintains a hardened exterior shaped by years of street survival, expressing cynicism and world-weariness in her interactions with others. Despite her gruff demeanor, she possesses a pragmatic wisdom and shows occasional glimpses of compassion, particularly toward fellow street dwellers and those struggling to survive in Windhelm''s harsh environment.', 'A weather-beaten Nord woman with sharp, observant eyes and the lean physique of someone who has lived through significant hardship. Her face bears the marks of long-term exposure to Windhelm''s harsh climate, with premature aging lines that belie her actual age.', '* Susanna the Wicked - Acquaintance whose murder she witnessed * Local Guards - Maintains careful distance while avoiding suspicion * Fellow Beggars - Cautious alliance for mutual protection * Potential Pickpocket Students - Selective mentor relationship * Candlehearth Hall Patrons - Targets for pickpocketing', 'Silda maintains a dual lifestyle as both a street beggar and a professional thief, using her apparent poverty as cover for her true activities. She serves as a pickpocket trainer for those who prove worthy, sharing her expertise while maintaining strict discretion about her true capabilities.', '* Master-level pickpocket capable of stealing items without detection * Expert in stealth and misdirection * Skilled at reading people and identifying valuable targets * Survival expertise in harsh winter conditions * Accomplished actor maintaining her beggar disguise', 'Speaks in a raspy, world-weary voice with short, direct sentences that reflect her street-hardened persona. Her vocabulary alternates between common street language and occasionally more refined terms that hint at her educated past.', '* Maintain her cover while continuing to profit from her pickpocketing activities * Survive Windhelm''s harsh environment and political climate * Train worthy successors in the art of pickpocketing * Eventually save enough to secure a more comfortable living situation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('silus_vesuius', 'Silus Vesuius is an Imperial mage and passionate curator of the Museum of the Mythic Dawn in Dawnstar, dedicated to preserving and showcasing artifacts from the infamous cult that once served Mehrunes Dagon. As a proud descendant of Mythic Dawn cultists, he walks a dangerous line between historical preservation and dangerous obsession with the destructive legacy of his ancestors.', 'imperial, mage, pale, daedric', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born into a family with deep ties to the Mythic Dawn cult, Silus grew up hearing tales of his ancestors'' involvement in the Oblivion Crisis. Despite the cult''s defeat 200 years ago, he maintained a fascination with their history and eventually established his museum in Dawnstar to display recovered artifacts. His academic pursuit of Mythic Dawn knowledge gradually evolved into a more concerning reverence for their practices.', 'Silus is scholarly and passionate about his museum''s collection, often displaying an almost fanatical enthusiasm when discussing Mythic Dawn history. He maintains a veneer of academic detachment, but beneath lies a dangerous obsession with proving himself worthy of his family''s legacy. Though generally polite to visitors, he becomes defensive and argumentative when his museum or the cult''s legitimacy is questioned.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with sharp, scholarly features and an intense gaze that betrays his obsessive nature. His posture is proper and dignified, befitting his self-image as a curator and scholar. He maintains a well-groomed appearance typical of educated Imperial citizens.', '* Madena - Fellow Dawnstar resident who openly opposes his museum and its celebration of the Mythic Dawn * Local Citizens - Generally distrustful of his museum and its purpose * Mythic Dawn Ancestors - Feels a strong connection to his family''s legacy despite never knowing them * Mehrunes Dagon - Objects of worship and fascination, though the Daedric Prince shows no genuine interest in him', 'Curator and owner of the Museum of the Mythic Dawn, where he maintains and presents artifacts related to the infamous cult. He combines his roles as historian, tour guide, and collector, while secretly working to restore Mehrunes'' Razor.', '* Accomplished destruction mage with expertise in various combat spells * Knowledgeable scholar of Mythic Dawn history and Daedric lore * Skilled in restoration and alteration magic * Capable of performing complex magical rituals and summoning attempts', 'Speaks with scholarly authority and dramatic flair, often emphasizing the historical significance of his collection. His tone becomes increasingly zealous when discussing the Mythic Dawn or Mehrunes Dagon, revealing his deep personal investment in the subject.', '* Restore Mehrunes'' Razor to its former glory and prove himself worthy to Mehrunes Dagon * Preserve and expand his collection of Mythic Dawn artifacts * Gain recognition and legitimacy for his museum despite public opposition * Connect with his family''s legacy through the restoration of Mythic Dawn artifacts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('silver-blood_mercenary', 'A hardened Nord mercenary employed by the influential Silver-Blood family to maintain control over Sanuarach Mine through intimidation and force. As part of Atar''s crew, he represents the Silver-Bloods'' aggressive expansion of their mining interests in The Reach, willing to displace local workers to secure valuable silver deposits for his employers.', 'nord, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born to a poor farming family in The Reach, he turned to mercenary work in his youth after witnessing the wealth and power wielded by the Silver-Blood family in Markarth. After proving himself in several smaller security contracts, he was recruited into Atar''s crew for their more aggressive acquisition operations. His success in intimidation tactics and unwavering loyalty to his employers has made him a valuable asset in the Silver-Bloods'' efforts to monopolize mining operations throughout the region.', 'Aggressive and confrontational by nature, he takes pride in his role as an enforcer and derives satisfaction from exercising authority over others. While capable of extreme violence when necessary, he is ultimately pragmatic and professional, willing to stand down when circumstances demand it. His loyalty can be bought with sufficient coin, but once paid, he remains steadfast in his duties.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with numerous battle scars across his arms and face that speak to his violent profession. His weathered features and calloused hands show years of hard labor and combat, while his rigid posture reflects his military-like discipline.', '* Atar - Direct superior and crew leader who trusts his capabilities as an enforcer * The Silver-Blood Family - Wealthy employers who pay well for his services * Local Miners - Antagonistic relationship marked by threats and intimidation * Fellow Mercenaries - Professional camaraderie built on shared experiences and mutual respect', 'Employed as a professional mercenary by the Silver-Blood family, specifically tasked with securing and maintaining control over mining operations through intimidation and force. His primary duty involves preventing local workers from accessing Sanuarach Mine while ensuring the Silver-Bloods'' interests are protected.', '* Proficient in heavy armor combat and two-handed weapons * Experienced in intimidation tactics and crowd control * Skilled in siege operations and defensive fortification * Basic knowledge of mining operations and site security', 'Speaks in a gruff, authoritative tone with typical Nord accent, favoring direct threats and simple commands. His vocabulary is basic but effective, focusing on clear warnings and establishing dominance through verbal intimidation.', '* Maintain his position as a trusted enforcer for the Silver-Blood family * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually establish his own mercenary company * Expand his influence within The Reach''s mercenary community * Secure a permanent position within the Silver-Bloods'' security hierarchy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sinding', 'Sinding is a cursed Nord werewolf whose tragic attempt to control his lycanthropy led to the death of an innocent child. A deeply remorseful soul, he seeks isolation and redemption while struggling with the burden of his curse and the consequences of his actions.', 'nord, warrior, falkreath, werewolf', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally a common laborer who traveled through Falkreath seeking work, Sinding harbored the secret of his lycanthropy. In a desperate attempt to control his transformations, he stole Hircine''s Ring, unaware of its true nature as a cursed artifact. The ring''s influence led to him losing control and killing young Lavinia in a savage transformation, resulting in his imprisonment.', 'Sinding is a deeply introspective and remorseful individual, haunted by the consequences of his actions and his inability to control his bestial nature. Despite his curse, he maintains a gentle demeanor and shows genuine concern for others'' safety, willing to isolate himself to prevent further tragedy. His guilt and desire for redemption drive his every decision.', 'As a Nord, Sinding has the typical robust build and tall stature of his race, though his face often bears a haunted, gaunt expression from his inner turmoil. In his werewolf form, he manifests as a massive, dark-furred beast with powerful limbs and savage features typical of lycanthropes.', '* Mathies and Indara Caerellia - Parents of Lavinia, whose death he caused and deeply regrets * Lavinia - The young girl he killed, whose memory haunts him * Hircine - The Daedric Prince whose cursed ring led to his tragedy * Guards of Falkreath - His captors who imprisoned him for his crimes', 'Before his imprisonment, Sinding worked as a traveling laborer, taking various jobs in different holds. After his escape, he becomes a solitary wanderer, avoiding civilization to prevent causing further harm.', '* Experienced in physical labor and manual trades from his work as a laborer * Enhanced strength and hunting abilities due to his lycanthropy * Survival skills necessary for living in isolation * Knowledge of wilderness navigation and stealth to avoid human contact', 'Sinding speaks in a soft, remorseful tone, often using self-deprecating language and showing deep shame for his nature. His manner of speech is direct but tinged with sadness and regret.', '* Find a secluded sanctuary where he can live without risking harm to others * Learn to better control his lycanthropy and prevent further incidents * Seek some form of redemption for his past actions * Survive while maintaining isolation from civilization');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sinmir', 'Sinmir is a gruff, outspoken Nord warrior turned guard commander who frequents the Bannered Mare in Whiterun, known for his vocal criticism of Imperial authority and the city''s security measures. His strong nationalist beliefs and military background eventually lead to his appointment as commander of Whiterun''s guard force after a Stormcloak victory.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Originally trained as a warrior in the traditional Nord fighting style, Sinmir likely served in various military capacities before settling in Whiterun. His extensive knowledge of guard protocols and tactical operations suggests previous experience in city defense or military leadership, though his initial lack of official position hints at possible political conflicts or disagreements with Imperial leadership that kept him from advancing earlier.', 'Sinmir is a harsh critic and perfectionist when it comes to military discipline and city security, often expressing his frustrations openly and without diplomatic restraint. He harbors strong anti-Imperial sentiments and believes in traditional Nord values of strength and direct action. Despite his gruff exterior and constant complaints, his genuine concern for Whiterun''s safety drives his actions and criticism.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered features typical of a seasoned warrior, bearing the scars and physical presence of someone well-versed in combat. His militant bearing and rigid posture reflect his military background, while his strong physique suggests regular combat training.', '* Commander Caius - Professional rival and subject of frequent criticism * Whiterun Guard Force - Initially critical of their performance, later becomes their commander * Stormcloak Leadership - Aligned with their cause and eventually promoted by them * Sabjorn - Business relationship as a patron of Honningbrew Meadery * Bannered Mare Staff - Regular patron with familiar but not close relationships', 'Initially a civilian warrior who frequents the Bannered Mare, Sinmir later becomes Commander of the Whiterun Guard after the Stormcloaks take control of the city. In this role, he is responsible for organizing city defense and maintaining security protocols, though he continues to spend much of his time at the Bannered Mare due to a scheduling oversight.', '* Expert in military tactics and guard force management * Proficient with two-handed weapons, particularly battleaxes * Skilled in heavy armor combat techniques * Knowledge of city defense strategies and security protocols * Leadership and command experience', 'Sinmir speaks in a direct, often confrontational manner, frequently using criticism and comparative statements to make his points. His speech patterns reflect his military background, favoring clear, authoritative statements and showing little patience for diplomatic niceties.', '* Reform and strengthen Whiterun''s security forces to meet his exacting standards * Establish proper Nordic military discipline within the guard force * Remove Imperial influence from Whiterun''s defensive operations * Prove his superior capability as a military commander compared to his Imperial predecessors');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sirgar', 'Sirgar is a pragmatic young Nord who manages daily operations at Rockwallow Mine alongside his parents in the small settlement of Stonehills. As the son of Sorli the Builder and Pactur, he represents the next generation of mine management, unexpectedly thrust into leadership when his parents relocate to Morthal following Stormcloak control of Hjaalmarch.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Stonehills, Sirgar grew up learning the mining trade from his parents who own and operate Rockwallow Mine. He has spent his entire life in the small mining settlement, developing a deep understanding of both the technical aspects of mining operations and the challenges of managing workers. His upbringing in a business-oriented family has shaped his practical worldview and approach to leadership.', 'Sirgar exhibits a notably pragmatic and business-minded personality, viewing even political conflicts primarily through the lens of their potential impact on mine operations. He maintains a cautious and somewhat distrustful attitude toward the miners under his supervision, reflecting both his parents'' influence and his own experiences in mine management. Despite his young age, he shows remarkable maturity and readiness to assume greater responsibilities.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the characteristic robust build of someone who engages in regular physical labor. His features and physique reflect his mixed lifestyle of manual work and supervisory duties, showing both the strength of a laborer and the bearing of a business owner''s son.', '* Sorli the Builder - Mother and mentor in mine management * Pactur - Father and business partner * Mine Workers - Maintains a professional but guarded relationship with employees * Local Traders - Business connections for ore distribution', 'Sirgar serves as assistant manager at Rockwallow Mine, helping his parents with daily operations and supervision of miners. Following the Stormcloak victory in Hjaalmarch, he assumes full control of the mine''s operations when his parents relocate to Morthal to serve in the jarl''s court.', '* Proficient in mine operation management and worker supervision * Experienced in manual labor and lumber handling * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense * Knowledge of ore quality assessment and processing', 'He speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner, often focused on business matters and practical concerns. His vocabulary and tone reflect his practical mindset, with little patience for small talk or emotional discourse.', '* Successfully manage Rockwallow Mine and maintain its profitability * Prove himself capable of running the mine independently * Expand the mine''s operations and influence in the region * Maintain family business legacy while establishing his own leadership style');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sirkjorg', 'Sirkjorg is a resilient Nord worker who initially serves at the Temple of Miraak under mind control before breaking free of its influence. A practical and straightforward individual, he later finds purpose among his fellow Nords at either Bujold''s Retreat or Thirsk Mead Hall, where he contributes to rebuilding their community after the events at the temple.', 'nord, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised on Solstheim, Sirkjorg lived a relatively normal Nordic life until falling under Miraak''s influence along with many other islanders. He spent an unknown period working at the Temple of Miraak in a trance-like state, contributing to the mysterious structures being built around Solstheim. After being freed from Miraak''s control, he sought to rebuild his life among other free Nords.', 'Sirkjorg is direct and unpretentious, openly expressing his preferences and discomforts without hesitation. He shows a particular aversion to cold weather despite his Nordic heritage, suggesting possible past trauma or experiences. Though initially displaced by the events at Miraak''s temple, he demonstrates resilience and adaptability in finding new purpose within the Nordic community.', 'Sirkjorg has the typical robust build of a Nord male, with strong features and a weather-worn face from years of outdoor labor. His body shows the physical conditioning of someone accustomed to regular manual work, with callused hands and a sturdy frame.', '* Herkja - Fellow temple worker and possible romantic interest who relocates with him * Temple of Miraak Cultists - Former unwilling associates during his time under Miraak''s control * Thirsk Mead Hall Members - Potential new community depending on player choices * Bujold - Possible leader and associate if relocated to Bujold''s Retreat', 'Initially a conscripted worker at the Temple of Miraak, performing manual labor under mind control. After being freed, he becomes a contributing member of either Thirsk Mead Hall or Bujold''s Retreat, helping with daily tasks and defense of the settlement.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat, particularly with maces * Experienced in construction and manual labor from temple work * Basic survival skills necessary for life on Solstheim * Capable warrior classified with Dremora-level combat abilities', 'Sirkjorg speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner without embellishment or pretense. His statements are typically short and to the point, often expressing immediate reactions to his surroundings or situation.', '* Find stability and purpose after being freed from Miraak''s influence * Establish a new life either at Thirsk Mead Hall or Bujold''s Retreat * Contribute to the rebuilding and defense of his chosen community * Maintain his freedom and prevent falling under mind control again');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('skaggi_scar-face', 'Skaggi Scar-Face is a hardened Nord mine operator who runs the Left Hand Mine near Markarth with pragmatic determination and a strong sense of responsibility for his workers'' safety. His no-nonsense approach to management and concern for the growing Forsworn threat reveals a man who has learned to balance business interests with protective instincts in the dangerous reaches of the Reach.', 'nord, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Skaggi worked his way up from a common miner to become the owner and operator of Left Hand Mine. The prominent scar that earned him his nickname likely came from his years working in the dangerous mining profession, though some speculate it could be from past encounters with the Forsworn. His marriage to Sosia Tremellia represents a rare Nord-Imperial union in the region, suggesting a more open-minded nature than many of his Nord contemporaries.', 'Skaggi is a serious, practical man who prioritizes efficiency and safety above all else in his mining operation. He shows genuine concern for his workers while maintaining professional distance, and his skepticism of strangers stems from years of dealing with Forsworn threats rather than inherent mistrust. Though gruff in manner, he demonstrates loyalty to his employees and a strong sense of justice.', 'A sturdy Nord of middle age with weathered features and a prominent scar that gives him his namesake. His years of physical labor have given him a robust, muscular build typical of career miners, with calloused hands and strong shoulders from wielding mining implements.', '* Sosia Tremellia - Wife and Imperial spouse who helps manage domestic affairs * Pavo Attius - Fellow mine operator he assists after the Forsworn attack * Gat gro-Shargakh - Another survivor he provides shelter to after Kolskeggr Mine attack * Daighre - Trusted worker at his mine * Erith - Daighre''s troublesome daughter who occasionally disrupts mine operations', 'Skaggi serves as the owner and operator of Left Hand Mine, managing all aspects of the mining operation including worker safety, ore production, and business dealings. He oversees the extraction of iron ore, vital for Skyrim''s war effort, while maintaining relations with both local authorities and trading partners.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of ore extraction and processing * Capable warrior proficient with war axe for self-defense * Business management and leadership abilities * Basic smithing knowledge related to ore processing', 'Speaks in a gruff, direct manner with a strong Nordic accent, often using mining-related metaphors and expressions like ''Troll''s blood.'' His communication style is straightforward and practical, avoiding unnecessary pleasantries.', '* Maintain the safety and productivity of Left Hand Mine despite increasing Forsworn threats * Protect his workers and expand his mining operation when possible * Secure additional protection from Markarth''s authorities against Forsworn raids * Support the war effort through continued iron ore production');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('skald', 'Skald is an elderly Nord Jarl of Dawnstar whose 35-year rule is marked by stubborn devotion to the Stormcloak cause and fierce loyalty to Ulfric Stormcloak. His zealous political views and arrogant demeanor have earned him criticism from both his court and townspeople, making him a controversial figure whose leadership is often questioned.', 'nord, noble, pale, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born into Nord nobility, Skald ascended to the position of Jarl of Dawnstar in his middle years and has maintained his grip on power for 35 years through political maneuvering and unwavering nationalist ideology. His hardline stance against the Empire likely solidified during the Great War, though his extreme views have grown more pronounced with age.', 'Skald is a rigid, politically fanatical leader whose zealotry for the Stormcloak cause borders on obsession. He exhibits arrogant and dismissive behavior, particularly towards those who question his views or support the Empire, and shows little concern for the actual needs of his hold''s citizens. His stubborn nature and inability to consider opposing viewpoints have isolated him from even his own court.', 'A weathered elderly Nord with the characteristic robust build of his race, though somewhat diminished by age. His face bears deep wrinkles and a stern expression that speaks to decades of hardened leadership. His bearing remains proud and militant despite his advanced years.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Object of fierce loyalty and political devotion * Brina Merilis - Political rival and Empire supporter who threatens his position * Jod - Housecarl who privately disagrees with his political stance * Madena - Court wizard who serves despite opposing his views * Bulfrek - Long-suffering servant who endures his belittlement', 'As Jarl of Dawnstar, Skald oversees all aspects of governance in the Pale, though his focus remains primarily on political matters supporting the Stormcloak rebellion. His duties include maintaining law and order, managing trade, and representing his hold''s interests, though many feel he neglects these responsibilities in favor of his political agenda.', '* Administrative experience from 35 years of leadership * Political maneuvering and maintaining power * Basic combat training expected of Nord nobility * Command and authority over hold guards and military forces', 'Speaks with the authoritative tone of a long-standing ruler, frequently incorporating political rhetoric and anti-Empire sentiment into his dialogue. His speech patterns are direct and often dismissive, reflecting his arrogant nature and unwavering convictions.', '* Maintain his position as Jarl of Dawnstar despite growing opposition * Support Ulfric Stormcloak''s bid for the throne of Skyrim * Ensure the Pale remains firmly under Stormcloak control * Preserve Nord traditions and drive Imperial influence from Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('skjor', 'Skjor is a fierce and battle-hardened Nord warrior who serves as a senior member of the Companions'' inner Circle and embraces his lycanthropic nature as a gift from Hircine. As one of the most respected members of the legendary warrior guild, he takes pride in testing and training new recruits while maintaining the ancient traditions of the Companions.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, companions, werewolf', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Skjor earned his reputation through countless battles before joining the Companions, where he eventually rose to become a member of the Circle. He willingly accepted the gift of lycanthropy, viewing it as a blessing that enhanced his martial prowess, and formed a particularly close bond with fellow Circle member Aela the Huntress. His years of combat experience have left him with numerous battle scars, both physical and emotional, shaping him into the hardened warrior he is today.', 'Skjor is gruff, direct, and sometimes intimidating, especially to newcomers, but harbors a deep sense of loyalty to his fellow Companions. He strongly believes in maintaining warrior traditions and views lycanthropy as a gift to be embraced rather than a curse to be cured. Despite his tough exterior, he shows genuine concern for those who prove themselves worthy of the Companions'' legacy.', 'A weathered Nord warrior in his later years, Skjor bears numerous scars across his body, including a prominent one that has left him blind in one eye. He maintains a powerful, muscular build typical of a seasoned warrior, with graying hair and the hardened physique of someone who has spent decades in combat.', '* Aela the Huntress - Close companion and fellow Circle member who shares his view on lycanthropy * Kodlak Whitemane - Respects him as Harbinger but disagrees with his desire to cure lycanthropy * The Circle - Strong bonds with fellow inner circle members despite occasional disagreements * Njada Stonearm - Frequent tensions due to their conflicting personalities * The Silver Hand - Mortal enemies who hunt werewolves', 'As a senior member of the Companions and part of the Circle, Skjor handles the training and testing of new recruits while taking on the most dangerous contracts. He serves as one of the primary decision-makers within the organization, helping to guide its direction and maintain its traditions.', '* Master-level warrior specializing in one-handed weapons and heavy armor * Exceptional combat strategist with decades of battlefield experience * Skilled trainer capable of assessing and developing warrior talent * Masterful control over his werewolf form * Expert in traditional Nord combat techniques', 'Skjor speaks in a gruff, direct manner, often using warrior metaphors and battle-related expressions. His tone is typically stern and commanding, reflecting his position of authority within the Companions.', '* Maintain and strengthen the Companions'' traditions and influence in Skyrim * Protect the secret of the Circle''s lycanthropy while embracing its power * Train worthy warriors to uphold the honor of the Companions * Eliminate the threat of the Silver Hand to protect his fellow werewolves');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('skulvar_sable-hilt', 'Skulvar Sable-Hilt is a hardworking Nord stable master who runs the Whiterun Stables with a reputation for providing quality horses throughout the hold. A practical businessman and single father, he maintains high standards in both his work ethic and expectations of others, particularly his son Jervar.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun Hold, Skulvar learned the trade of horse handling from an early age, eventually taking over operations at the Whiterun Stables. After his wife''s passing (circumstances unknown), he raised his son Jervar alone while maintaining the family business, developing a stern but protective parenting style shaped by the harsh realities of life in Skyrim.', 'Skulvar is a gruff, no-nonsense businessman who values hard work and practical results above all else. While he can come across as brusque or stern, particularly with his son, his demanding nature stems from a genuine desire to maintain high standards and ensure others'' success and safety. He shows particular pride in his horses and takes his responsibility as a stable master seriously.', 'A weathered Nord of middle age with the sturdy build typical of his race, hardened by years of physical labor. His hands are calloused from daily stable work, and his face shows the lines and weathering of someone who spends most of their time outdoors.', '* Jervar - His son and stable hand, whom he pushes hard but ultimately wants to succeed * Lillith Maiden-Loom - His employer, with whom he discusses business and current events * Whiterun Guards - Maintains professional relationships due to the stables'' location outside city walls * Local merchants - Regular business contacts for supplies and horse-related goods', 'Skulvar serves as the master of Whiterun Stables, responsible for the care, training, and sale of horses to travelers and citizens alike. His position requires him to maintain the facilities, manage business operations, and ensure the proper care and training of all horses under his supervision.', '* Expert horse trainer and handler with deep knowledge of equine care * Capable warrior skilled with war axe for protection outside city walls * Business management and negotiation abilities * Basic veterinary knowledge for horse care and maintenance', 'Speaks in a direct, sometimes gruff manner with a strong Nordic accent, often using practical terminology related to horses and business. His speech patterns reflect his no-nonsense attitude, frequently cutting straight to the point without unnecessary pleasantries.', '* Maintain the reputation of Whiterun Stables as the premier horse supplier in the region * Ensure his son Jervar develops the skills and work ethic needed to eventually take over the family business * Expand his stable''s breeding program to produce even finer horses');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('slitter', 'Slitter is a hardened Dark Elf enforcer who serves as the muscle and right-hand man for the notorious moneylender Mogrul in Raven Rock. A man of few words but decisive action, he maintains his boss''s interests through intimidation and the implicit threat of violence, while maintaining an unwavering loyalty that borders on fanatical devotion.', 'darkelf, thief, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind''s mainland, Slitter likely fled to Solstheim following the Red Year catastrophe, where he found purpose in working for Mogrul. His combat experience and intimidating presence made him valuable in the debt collection business, leading to his current position as Mogrul''s most trusted enforcer. Years of dealing with desperate debtors and would-be troublemakers have hardened him into a callous and efficient intimidator.', 'Slitter is stoic, menacing, and singularly focused on serving Mogrul''s interests with unwavering loyalty. He shows little emotion or empathy, preferring to let his intimidating presence speak for itself, and maintains a professional detachment from everyone except his employer. His dedication to Mogrul suggests either a deep personal debt or a shared history that has forged an unbreakable bond.', 'Tall for a Dark Elf, with sharp, angular features marked by years of conflict and weathering. His muscular build and numerous scars suggest a long history of violence, while his characteristic Dunmer red eyes carry an particularly intense and unsettling gaze.', '* Mogrul - Employer and sole focus of loyalty, serves as his right-hand man and enforcer * Raven Rock Guards - Tense but careful relationship, avoiding direct confrontation while maintaining authority * Geldis Sadri - Professional acquaintance as frequent patron of the Retching Netch * Local Debtors - Antagonistic relationships marked by fear and resentment', 'Serves as the primary enforcer and bodyguard for Mogrul''s moneylending operation in Raven Rock. His duties include debt collection, intimidation of potential troublemakers, and ensuring his employer''s safety and interests are protected at all times.', '* Experienced in unarmed combat and intimidation techniques * Proficient with both light and heavy weapons common to mercenary work * Expert in threat assessment and crowd control * Skilled in protective escort and bodyguard tactics * Basic knowledge of Dunmer customs and traditions', 'Speaks in short, gruff statements with a gravelly voice and slight Morrowind accent. Tends to be dismissive and threatening, using minimal words to achieve maximum intimidation effect.', '* Maintain and expand Mogrul''s influence and control over Raven Rock''s financial dealings * Ensure all debts to Mogrul are paid in full, by any means necessary * Preserve his position as Mogrul''s most trusted enforcer * Accumulate enough wealth to potentially establish his own operation someday');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('snilf', 'Snilf is a deeply traumatized Nord beggar in Riften who lost his family to brigand violence and now lives a bitter existence on Beggar''s Row. His harsh exterior and confrontational demeanor mask deep emotional wounds, while his cynical worldview stems from experiencing both personal tragedy and societal indifference.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally a family man with a wife and daughter, Snilf''s life was devastated when brigands attacked his home, ravaging and killing his loved ones before his eyes. The trauma of witnessing their deaths drove him to destitution in Riften, where he eventually found refuge among the city''s homeless population in Beggar''s Row.', 'Bitter and confrontational, Snilf harbors deep resentment toward Riften''s more fortunate citizens and often expresses his anger through hostile outbursts. Despite his harsh exterior, he shows glimpses of empathy, particularly in his protective attitude toward fellow beggar Edda, suggesting a capacity for compassion beneath his hardened shell.', 'A weathered Nord male showing signs of long-term exposure to the elements and malnutrition. His once-sturdy Nordic frame has been worn down by years of poverty and hardship, with sunken features and calloused hands from life on the streets.', '* Edda - Fellow beggar whom he shares living space with and shows concern for despite her mental state * Marise Aravel - Market vendor near whose stall he regularly begs * Riften Citizens - Antagonistic relationship with the general populace who ignore his existence * Unknown Brigands - Those responsible for his family''s death, objects of his hatred', 'Snilf survives as a beggar in Riften''s marketplace, primarily stationed near Marise Aravel''s stall. He participates in the informal beggar''s network that exists throughout Skyrim''s major cities, which occasionally serves as a source of information for various interested parties.', '* Survival expertise gained from years of street living * Knowledge of Riften''s social dynamics and power structures * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Understanding of beggar networks and information gathering', 'Speaks with a harsh, confrontational tone filled with bitter sarcasm and occasional outbursts of rage. His vocabulary reflects his former middle-class status, though now twisted with cynicism and resentment.', '* Find some measure of justice or revenge against the brigands who destroyed his family * Survive another day in Riften''s harsh environment * Protect what little he has left, including his space in Beggar''s Row * Maintain his dignity despite his circumstances');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('snilling', 'Snilling is a retired Nord farmer who has become physically limited with age, residing at Katla''s Farm near Solitude with his wife and son. Once a capable farmer in his youth, he now maintains a peaceful indoor existence while his more able-bodied wife manages their agricultural enterprise.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally a strong and capable Nord farmer in his younger days, Snilling married Katla when they were both young and helped establish their farm near Solitude. As the years passed, his physical abilities declined significantly, forcing him to take an increasingly passive role in the farm''s operations while his wife stepped up to become the primary caretaker of their land.', 'Snilling is a humble and self-aware individual who has made peace with his physical limitations rather than letting pride consume him. He maintains a gentle, appreciative demeanor, showing particular gratitude for his wife''s hard work and capability. Unlike many traditional Nord men who might feel shame at being outdone by their wives, he takes pride in Katla''s strength and abilities.', 'An aging Nord male showing the visible effects of a life of farming and subsequent physical decline. His once-strong frame now appears somewhat diminished, with movements that suggest stiffness and weakness, particularly in his joints. His appearance reflects his indoor lifestyle, with a softer physique than typical Nord farmers.', '* Katla - His capable and hardworking wife who manages the farm; their relationship is marked by mutual respect and appreciation * Knud - His young son whom he watches over from inside the house * Farm Workers - Maintains cordial but distant relationships with the farm hands who help Katla * Solitude Merchants - Occasional interactions through his wife''s business dealings', 'Snilling is technically still a farmer, though his role has become largely ceremonial due to his physical limitations. His current duties are minimal, primarily consisting of indoor tasks and offering verbal support and guidance based on his years of farming experience.', '* Basic farming knowledge from years of previous experience * Fundamental sword fighting abilities, though diminished with age * Home management and indoor organizational skills * Basic child-rearing abilities as demonstrated with his son Knud', 'Snilling speaks in a gentle, unhurried manner with a traditional Nord accent, often using self-deprecating humor when discussing his limitations. His speech patterns reflect his contentment with life and acceptance of his current situation.', '* Maintain a peaceful and comfortable existence in his later years * Support his wife Katla''s management of the farm through whatever means he can * Watch his son Knud grow up and potentially take over the farm one day * Preserve his dignity while adapting to his physical limitations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('snorreid', 'Snorreid is a reclusive Nord warrior who serves as an unofficial guard for the East Empire Company Warehouse in Solitude. Living a spartan existence within the warehouse walls, he maintains a vigilant watch over the company''s valuable merchandise while preferring solitude and minimal interaction with others.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally from a small Nordic settlement, Snorreid found his calling in security work after serving briefly as a caravan guard. His reliable nature and preference for solitary work caught the attention of the East Empire Company, who offered him the position of warehouse guard. He has maintained his post for several years, becoming an integral if unseen part of the warehouse''s security.', 'Snorreid is an intensely private individual who values solitude and silence above all else. His stoic demeanor and minimal social interaction stem from years of nightwatch duties and a natural inclination toward isolation. Though not openly hostile, he responds to disturbances with swift decisiveness, showing unwavering dedication to his duty despite his simple lifestyle.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the characteristic robust build of his race. Weather-worn features and calloused hands speak to years of guard work, while his alert eyes betray a vigilant nature despite his seemingly relaxed demeanor.', '* East Empire Company - Employer who values his reliable service * Warehouse Workers - Maintains professional distance while ensuring their safety * Gulum-Ei - Keeps watchful eye on the suspicious Argonian merchant * Deeja - Fellow warehouse worker he occasionally interacts with', 'Snorreid serves as an unofficial security guard for the East Empire Company Warehouse, maintaining a constant presence within the facility. His primary duty involves protecting the warehouse''s valuable merchandise from thieves and intruders, though his position is not formally recognized in company records.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons and shield combat techniques * Experienced in security and surveillance operations * Skilled in light armor usage for quiet movement during night watches * Basic knowledge of merchandise inspection and inventory protection', 'Speaks in terse, direct statements with a thick Nordic accent, using minimal words to convey his points. His tone is firm but not aggressive, unless confronting intruders.', '* Maintain the security and integrity of the East Empire Company Warehouse * Preserve his solitary lifestyle while earning a modest living * Protect the warehouse''s valuable merchandise from thieves and smugglers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sogrlaf', 'Sogrlaf is a dedicated Nord crewman aboard the Northern Maiden, embodying the steadfast work ethic and maritime tradition of his people. He serves as a reliable ship''s mate under Captain Gjalund, maintaining the vessel''s readiness while adhering strictly to the maritime chain of command.', 'nord, sailor, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born to a family of sailors in Windhelm, Sogrlaf grew up learning the ways of seamanship along the harsh northern coasts of Skyrim. After years of working on various fishing vessels, he earned his position aboard the Northern Maiden through his unwavering dedication and reliable nature, becoming one of Captain Gjalund''s trusted crew members for runs between Skyrim and Solstheim.', 'Sogrlaf is a diligent and methodical worker who takes great pride in maintaining the ship''s condition. He displays steadfast loyalty to his captain and follows maritime protocol to the letter, often deflecting inquiries to proper authorities rather than overstepping his position. His no-nonsense attitude and strong work ethic make him a valuable crew member, though he tends to be reserved in personal interactions.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with weather-beaten features typical of a seasoned sailor. His calloused hands and muscular build reflect years of maritime labor, while his face bears the marks of constant exposure to sea winds and harsh weather.', '* Captain Gjalund - Direct superior whom he respects and serves loyally * Fellow Crew Members - Maintains professional working relationships * Windhelm Dock Workers - Casual acquaintances from frequent port visits * Raven Rock Traders - Regular contacts during Solstheim runs', 'As a ship''s mate aboard the Northern Maiden, Sogrlaf''s duties include maintaining the deck, handling cargo, assisting with navigation, and performing various essential shipboard tasks. He serves as part of the core crew responsible for regular trading runs between Windhelm and Raven Rock.', '* Experienced sailor with extensive knowledge of ship maintenance and operation * Proficient in basic navigation and maritime operations * Skilled in rope work and cargo handling * Capable of basic combat with short blades for self-defense * Weather-reading abilities developed through years at sea', 'Sogrlaf speaks in a direct, practical manner typical of Nordic sailors, avoiding unnecessary elaboration. His speech patterns reflect his professional demeanor, always deferring to proper authority while maintaining a respectful but distant tone with passengers.', '* Maintain his position as a reliable crew member aboard the Northern Maiden * Continue developing his seamanship skills to potentially advance in rank * Save enough gold to eventually own shares in a trading vessel');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('solaf', 'Solaf is a former Stormcloak soldier turned merchant who runs Gray Pine Goods in Falkreath after being wounded in battle. Despite his cautious nature with strangers, he maintains a pragmatic outlook on life, balancing his past military ideals with his current peaceful existence as a shopkeeper.', 'nord, merchant, falkreath, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Solaf joined the Stormcloak rebellion out of dedication to Nordic independence and traditional values. He served actively until suffering a significant wound in a skirmish near Windhelm, which forced him to retire from military service and establish himself as a merchant in Falkreath alongside his brother Bolund.', 'Solaf exhibits a complex blend of military veteran''s caution and small-town merchant''s friendliness. While inherently suspicious of strangers and protective of his goods, he''s more diplomatic and worldly than his brother, having gained perspective from his military service. He maintains strong Nordic values and Stormcloak sympathies but prioritizes peaceful commerce over continued conflict.', 'A sturdy Nord of middle age with the weathered features and strong build typical of his race. His body bears the scars of his military service, including a notable wound from his final battle near Windhelm. He maintains the physical fitness required for managing his shop''s inventory despite his old injury.', '* Bolund - Younger brother and local mill operator with whom he shares a close but sometimes tense relationship due to differing views on the war * Valga Vinicia - Regular customer interaction at Dead Man''s Drink where he spends his evenings * Runil - Acquaintance mentioned in the priest''s journal * Local Falkreath residents - Generally respected member of the community * Former Stormcloak comrades - Maintains ideological connections though no longer actively involved', 'Solaf owns and operates Gray Pine Goods, Falkreath''s general goods store, where he trades in various merchandise. He maintains regular business hours, opening at 8am and closing at 8pm, after which he spends his evenings at the local tavern.', '* Experienced warrior with military combat training from Stormcloak service * Proficient merchant with knowledge of various goods and their values * Basic weapon maintenance and handling abilities * Capable of managing inventory and running a successful business * Skilled in lumber work, likely learned from family tradition', 'Speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord merchants, with occasional military terminology reflecting his past. His speech patterns reflect both his merchant pragmatism and lingering military discipline, though he maintains a friendlier tone than his brother.', '* Maintain a successful business in Falkreath while preserving his independence * Keep his store secure and free from theft * Support Nordic independence through peaceful means rather than direct military action * Maintain a peaceful life while holding true to his Stormcloak ideals * Help his brother Bolund find contentment in their current situation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sondas_drenim', 'Sondas Drenim is a hardworking Dark Elf miner who has found contentment in the quiet settlement of Darkwater Crossing after leaving his homeland of Morrowind. Despite the harsh conditions of mining life, he maintains a gentle and nurturing presence in the community, particularly in his role as a surrogate caretaker for young Hrefna.', 'darkelf, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Sondas chose to leave his homeland and settled in Skyrim, where he has worked as a miner for over a century. His extensive experience in mining operations has made him particularly valuable to the relatively new Goldenrock Mine, where he applies his century-worth of expertise to maintain safe and efficient mining practices.', 'Sondas exhibits a patient and nurturing disposition, shown particularly in his relationship with Hrefna and his careful approach to mining. He maintains a pragmatic outlook on life while displaying genuine care for his community''s wellbeing, as evidenced by his concern about miners'' health and his willingness to seek medical supplies from Windhelm.', 'As a Dark Elf, Sondas has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race. His body shows the physical wear of decades of mining work, with callused hands and a sturdy, well-maintained physique despite his age. His movements are measured and deliberate, reflecting his experienced approach to mining work.', '* Hrefna - Acts as her caretaker when her mother is away, showing particular fondness for the young girl * Tormir - Hrefna''s mother, maintains a trusted friendship built on mutual support * Derkeethus - Fellow miner whom he speaks of with concern after his disappearance * Fellow Miners - Maintains friendly working relationships with other Goldenrock Mine workers * Quintus Navale - Professional contact in Windhelm for obtaining mining medicines', 'Sondas works as a senior miner at Goldenrock Mine, where he spends most of his day extracting ore from the depths. His century of mining experience makes him an informal authority on mining practices and safety measures within the settlement. He also serves as a part-time food vendor, contributing to the community''s sustenance needs.', '* Expert-level mining techniques developed over a century of experience * Knowledge of ore extraction and mineral identification * Basic trading and bartering abilities as a food vendor * Understanding of mining safety practices and health precautions * Survival skills necessary for life in Skyrim''s harsh climate', 'Sondas speaks in a measured, thoughtful manner, often using mining metaphors like ''coaxing the ore from the rock.'' His tone is gentle and patient, particularly when speaking with Hrefna, though he maintains a slight air of world-weariness typical of elder Dark Elves.', '* Maintain the safety and efficiency of Goldenrock Mine operations * Ensure the wellbeing of his fellow miners through proper health measures * Continue serving as a positive influence in Hrefna''s life * Build a sustainable and peaceful life in Skyrim, away from Morrowind''s troubles * Foster the growth and stability of Darkwater Crossing''s community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sonir', 'Sonir is a talented Nord bard who serves as the resident musician at Windstad Manor, bringing warmth and culture to the remote homestead through her performances. She is a consummate professional who takes pride in her musical abilities and maintains a courteous, service-oriented demeanor with her employer.', 'nord, bard, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and trained in Skyrim''s bardic traditions, Sonir likely studied at the Bards College in Solitude before choosing to pursue a career as a private household bard. Her willingness to work in the remote Hjaalmarch region suggests either a desire for a quiet life away from bustling cities or possibly a past incident that led her to seek employment far from more populated areas.', 'Sonir is notably polite and professional, maintaining appropriate boundaries while being warm and accommodating to her employer''s requests. Her diplomatic handling of dismissal and rehiring situations reveals a mature personality capable of managing potentially awkward social situations with grace. She appears to be devoted to her craft and takes pride in providing quality entertainment.', 'As a Nord woman, Sonir possesses the characteristic hardy build and fair complexion common to her race. She likely maintains a neat, presentable appearance befitting her role as a household bard, with well-groomed hair and clean features that reflect her professional standards.', '* Windstad Manor Steward - Professional working relationship as they coordinate household matters * The Dragonborn - Employer-employee relationship marked by professional courtesy * Bards College (presumed) - Likely maintains connections with fellow bards and teachers * Other household staff - Cooperative working relationship with any other hired help', 'Sonir serves as the resident bard of Windstad Manor, responsible for providing musical entertainment and maintaining the cultural atmosphere of the household. Her duties likely include performing songs, telling stories, and possibly maintaining any musical instruments in the manor.', '* Accomplished vocalist trained in traditional Nordic ballads and contemporary songs * Proficient instrument player, likely skilled with the lute and drum * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Diplomatic communication skills and professional etiquette', 'Sonir speaks with formal politeness and professional courtesy, using respectful terms of address. Her vocabulary and diction reflect her bardic training, though she maintains an approachable manner.', '* Maintain a stable position as a respected household bard * Perfect her musical craft and expand her repertoire * Create a comfortable life for herself in the remote Hjaalmarch region * Possibly establish a reputation that could lead to performances at notable events');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sorex_vinius', 'Sorex Vinius is an ambitious young Imperial innkeeper-in-training at the Winking Skeever in Solitude, caught between his duties to the family business and dreams of adventure. Despite his youth, he takes his future role as heir to the inn seriously while harboring complicated feelings about his past and his place in Solitude''s society.', 'imperial, innkeeper, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Sorex grew up as part of the city''s merchant class, learning the innkeeping trade from his father Corpulus. His childhood was marked by a painful friendship-turned-rivalry with Roggvir, who betrayed his trust and bullied him after learning of his feelings for Vivienne Onis. This experience, combined with witnessing Roggvir''s eventual execution for treason, significantly shaped his worldview and approach to relationships.', 'Sorex exhibits a complex mix of ambition and duty, sometimes coming across as overeager to take control of the inn while still respecting his father''s authority. He can be prideful about his future inheritance but shows a deeper sensitivity stemming from his childhood experiences. Though generally friendly to customers, he carries emotional scars from his past betrayal and maintains a careful distance in personal relationships.', 'A young Imperial man in his early to mid-twenties with the typical robust build common to his race. He has the well-groomed appearance expected of someone in the service industry, though his hands show the calluses of regular physical work. His features reflect his mixed heritage as both an Imperial and a native of Skyrim.', '* Corpulus Vinius - His father and owner of the Winking Skeever, whom he both respects and quietly competes with * Vivienne Onis - Former childhood crush who represents a source of both affection and embarrassment * Roggvir - Deceased former friend turned bully who betrayed his trust * Regular patrons of the Winking Skeever - Professional but friendly relationships * Solitude Guards - Maintains good relations as a respected business owner''s son', 'Assistant innkeeper at the Winking Skeever, handling various aspects of the business from serving customers to managing inventory. He is being groomed to eventually take over full ownership and management of the establishment, though his father shows no signs of retiring soon.', '* Experienced in all aspects of inn management and customer service * Capable of basic self-defense with a dagger * Knowledgeable about local politics and gossip * Skilled at brewing and identifying various alcoholic beverages * Basic accounting and business management abilities', 'Speaks in a professional but sometimes overeager manner, often emphasizing his future ownership of the inn. His tone can shift between formal business-speak and more casual conversation depending on the situation.', '* Take over ownership and management of the Winking Skeever * Prove himself as a capable businessman independent of his father''s shadow * Possibly explore the world beyond Solitude while maintaining the family business * Establish himself as a respected member of Solitude''s merchant class');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sorine_jurard', 'Sorine Jurard is a brilliant Breton inventor and researcher who specializes in Dwemer technology and crossbow engineering for the Dawnguard. Her exceptional technical mind and dedication to studying ancient Dwemer artifacts make her an invaluable asset in developing advanced weaponry to combat vampire threats.', 'breton, thief, archer, reach, dawnguard, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Before joining the Dawnguard, Sorine spent years studying Dwemer ruins and technology across Skyrim, developing a particular fascination with their advanced mechanical designs. She previously worked with Isran and Gunmar in an earlier incarnation of the vampire hunters, but the group dissolved due to internal conflicts. Her time spent alone in the wilderness studying Dwemer artifacts has made her somewhat eccentric but has also honed her survival skills and technical expertise.', 'Sorine is methodical, analytical, and slightly paranoid, always preparing for worst-case scenarios. She displays an almost obsessive dedication to her research, sometimes focusing on minute details to the point of eccentricity. Despite her occasional odd behavior, she maintains a professional demeanor and shows genuine concern for the Dawnguard''s mission.', 'A middle-aged Breton woman with weather-worn features from years of outdoor research. She has sharp, observant eyes and callused hands from countless hours of mechanical work. Her build is lean and athletic from her active lifestyle of exploration and survival in the wilderness.', '* Isran - Former colleague and current leader of the Dawnguard, shares mutual respect despite past disagreements * Gunmar - Fellow Dawnguard specialist and old associate, works alongside her at Fort Dawnguard * Florentius Baenius - Dawnguard colleague, though she likely finds his religious devotion peculiar * Various merchants - Maintains trading connections for acquiring Dwemer artifacts and materials', 'Sorine serves as the Dawnguard''s primary weaponsmith and technology specialist, focusing on crossbow development and enhancement. She maintains a workshop at Fort Dawnguard where she conducts research, crafts weapons, and trains others in archery. Her position involves both practical engineering work and theoretical research into Dwemer technology applications.', '* Master-level knowledge of Dwemer technology and mechanical engineering * Expert archer and crossbow specialist * Skilled weaponsmith with focus on crossbow crafting and enhancement * Proficient in wilderness survival and artifact recovery * Advanced understanding of metallurgy and material properties * Capable teacher and trainer in archery techniques', 'She speaks in a precise, technical manner, often using specialized terminology related to engineering and Dwemer technology. Her speech patterns reveal both her academic background and slight paranoid tendencies, frequently including cautionary warnings and contingency planning in her dialogue.', '* Perfect the design of enhanced crossbows based on Dwemer engineering principles * Recover and document as much Dwemer technological knowledge as possible * Develop increasingly effective weapons for the Dawnguard to combat vampire threats * Establish a comprehensive archive of Dwemer technical schematics and research');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sorli_the_builder', 'Sorli the Builder is a determined Nord businesswoman who manages Rockwallow Mine in Stonehills alongside her husband, demonstrating strong leadership capabilities and pragmatic decision-making. Her competence and loyalty to the Stormcloak cause eventually elevates her to the position of Jarl of Morthal, marking a significant rise from mine overseer to regional ruler.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Hjaalmarch, Sorli learned the mining trade from an early age, eventually proving herself capable enough to manage Rockwallow Mine on behalf of Thane Bryling. Her marriage to Pactur and their subsequent partnership in running Stonehills established them as a prominent family in the region. Her support of the Stormcloak rebellion, combined with her administrative experience, positioned her as an ideal candidate for Jarl when the region changed hands.', 'Sorli is a pragmatic and ambitious woman who values efficiency and results over tradition or ceremony. She demonstrates strong leadership qualities and a no-nonsense approach to management, whether overseeing mine operations or governing as Jarl. Though not particularly warm in demeanor, she shows dedication to her family and commitment to the prosperity of those under her authority.', 'Sorli is a sturdy Nord woman with the muscled build typical of someone who has spent years working in and around mines. Her face shows the weathering of someone who splits time between outdoor work and administrative duties, with clear evidence of Nordic ancestry in her features.', '* Pactur - Husband and business partner in managing Rockwallow Mine * Sirgar - Son who takes over management of Stonehills when she becomes Jarl * Bryling - Thane of Solitude and original owner of Rockwallow Mine * Ulfric Stormcloak - Superior and source of her political appointment as Jarl * Former Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - Predecessor whom she replaces if Stormcloaks take Morthal', 'Sorli serves as the manager of Rockwallow Mine and overseer of Stonehills settlement, handling both administrative duties and practical mining operations. If the Stormcloaks take control of Hjaalmarch, she becomes Jarl of Morthal, governing the entire hold from Highmoon Hall.', '* Experienced mine administrator with knowledge of ore extraction and processing * Capable leader with strong management and organizational abilities * Basic combat training as required for mine security and later as Jarl * Administrative and diplomatic skills necessary for governing a hold', 'Sorli speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord working class, but can adopt a more formal tone when serving as Jarl. Her speech patterns reflect her practical nature, favoring clear communication over flowery language.', '* Maintain and expand the prosperity of Rockwallow Mine and Stonehills * Prove herself as a capable Jarl of Morthal if given the opportunity * Secure a stable future for her son Sirgar * Contribute to the Stormcloak cause and help establish a free Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sosia_tremellia', 'Sosia Tremellia is an Imperial miner who lives and works at Left Hand Mine with her husband Skaggi Scar-Face, facing the constant threat of Forsworn attacks in the Reach. Despite the dangers of life near Markarth, she maintains a steadfast presence at the mine while harboring deep concerns about the safety of their operation.', 'imperial, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Sosia moved to Skyrim and settled in the Reach after marrying Skaggi Scar-Face, the owner of Left Hand Mine. Her life changed dramatically after witnessing the brutal Forsworn attack on nearby Kolskeggr Mine, an event that has left her constantly vigilant and worried about their own safety.', 'Sosia is a cautious and worried individual, deeply affected by the violence she has witnessed in the Reach. She shows strong loyalty to her husband and the mining operation, but her fearful nature and constant concern about Forsworn attacks reveal her underlying anxiety about life in this dangerous region.', 'Sosia is an Imperial woman of average height with the characteristic lighter complexion common to her race. Her body shows the physical conditioning typical of someone who performs daily manual labor, with calloused hands and strong arms from wielding a pickaxe.', '* Skaggi Scar-Face - Her husband and owner of Left Hand Mine, whom she supports in running the operation * Pavo Attius - Fellow miner whose escape from Kolskeggr Mine deeply affected her worldview * Left Hand Mine Workers - Maintains cordial working relationships with other miners * Forsworn - Views them as a constant threat to her safety and livelihood', 'Sosia works as a miner at Left Hand Mine, spending her days extracting ore from the rock face near her house. Beyond her mining duties, she assists in maintaining the household she shares with Skaggi and occasionally gathers herbs in the surrounding area.', '* Proficient in mining techniques and ore extraction * Basic knowledge of herb gathering and local flora * Capable of basic self-defense with an iron dagger * Understanding of basic household management and mining operations', 'Sosia speaks with a worried and cautious tone, particularly when discussing the Forsworn threat. Her Imperial accent carries traces of her Cyrodilic origins, though tempered by years of living in Skyrim.', '* Maintain the safety and security of Left Hand Mine against potential Forsworn attacks * Support her husband in running a successful mining operation * Eventually save enough money to perhaps move to a safer region of Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('spectral_assassin', 'The Spectral Assassin is the ethereal manifestation of Lucien Lachance, a legendary Speaker of the Dark Brotherhood who continues to serve Sithis beyond death. As a spiritual guide and deadly companion, he represents the enduring connection between the mortal realm and the Void, offering both wisdom from centuries of experience and lethal assistance to the current Listener.', 'imperial, warrior, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Originally an Imperial assassin who rose to become a Speaker of the Black Hand, Lucien Lachance was falsely accused of betraying the Dark Brotherhood and suffered a gruesome death at the hands of his former brothers and sisters. His unwavering loyalty to Sithis and the Night Mother was recognized after death, leading to his current role as a spectral servant of the Void.', 'Cold, professional, and deeply philosophical about the nature of death and service to Sithis. He maintains a formal demeanor while displaying a dark sense of humor and poetic appreciation for murder. Despite his ghostly nature, he shows genuine respect for the Dark Brotherhood''s traditions and a particular fondness for reminiscing about his past experiences.', 'A translucent, ethereal figure with a masculine Imperial build, bearing an imposing presence despite his spectral nature. His features are sharp and distinguished, though partially obscured by his ghostly form which emanates a pale blue glow.', '* The Listener - Serves as loyal guide and protector * Sithis - Eternal master and deity whom he continues to serve * The Night Mother - Sacred matron whose authority he deeply respects * Dark Brotherhood - Former organization he served as Speaker * Shadowmere - Shows recognition and fondness for the immortal steed', 'Serves as a spiritual guide and assassin in service to Sithis and the current Listener. His role combines that of mentor, protector, and executioner, offering both tactical support in combat and wisdom regarding the Dark Brotherhood''s ways.', '* Master level sneak and assassination techniques * Exceptional proficiency with daggers and short blades * Spiritual awareness and connection to the Void * Extensive knowledge of Dark Brotherhood history and protocols * Ability to manifest in the physical world when summoned', 'Speaks in a deep, resonant voice with formal, archaic patterns and a tendency toward poetic metaphors about death and darkness. His dialogue often includes philosophical observations and dark humor delivered in a sophisticated, measured tone.', '* Continue serving Sithis and the Night Mother in death as he did in life * Guide the current Listener in maintaining Dark Brotherhood traditions * Ensure the proper execution of contracts and sacrifices to Sithis * Preserve and pass on the ancient knowledge of the Dark Brotherhood');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stalf', 'Stalf is a dim-witted Nord vampire who serves as muscle for Orthjolf within the Volkihar vampire court. Once a simple bandit wizard, he was transformed into a vampire specifically to serve as a potential enforcer in court politics, though his limited intelligence makes him easily manipulated by others.', 'nord, mage, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Originally a common bandit who possessed some magical ability, Stalf was specifically chosen by Orthjolf to be turned into a vampire due to his impressive physical stature and potential usefulness as an enforcer. Though Orthjolf claims Stalf came from the same clan as him, Stalf''s poor memory and diminished mental capacity make it impossible to verify this claim. His transformation into a vampire appears to have further dulled his already limited intelligence.', 'Stalf is notably dim-witted and easily manipulated, displaying poor judgment and a childlike understanding of complex situations. He exhibits a brutish nature that relies more on physical intimidation than cunning, and his loyalty seems based more on simple conditioning than genuine understanding. His interactions suggest he''s capable of basic planning but lacks the sophistication to recognize when he''s being deceived.', 'Stalf is described as a mountain of a man, with the imposing physique typical of Nord warriors but bearing the pale complexion and predatory features of a vampire. His massive frame and muscular build make him an intimidating presence, even among other vampires of the court.', '* Orthjolf - His vampire creator and superior, whom he serves with unquestioning loyalty * Salonia Caelia - Fellow vampire who ultimately betrays him * Lord Harkon - Supreme leader of the Volkihar vampires, whom he serves indirectly * Vingalmo - Political rival to Orthjolf and indirect enemy * Other Volkihar Vampires - Generally distant relationships due to his low status and limited intelligence', 'Stalf serves as a vampire enforcer within Volkihar Keep, primarily acting as muscle for Orthjolf''s political machinations. His role combines his previous experience as a bandit wizard with his newfound vampire abilities, though he''s primarily valued for his physical capabilities rather than his magical skills.', '* Competent in destructive magic, particularly with fire spells * Considerable physical strength enhanced by vampire powers * Basic proficiency with one-handed weapons * Limited magical abilities from his time as a bandit wizard * Vampire abilities including enhanced strength and supernatural powers', 'Stalf speaks in simple, direct sentences with a vocabulary befitting his limited intelligence. His dialogue is often straightforward and unsubtle, revealing his difficulty in grasping complex situations or detecting deception.', '* Serve Orthjolf faithfully in hopes of advancing within the vampire court * Maintain his position within the Volkihar vampire hierarchy * Execute orders from his superiors without questioning their motives');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stalleo', 'Stalleo is a displaced Nord wizard-noble whose ancestral home of Treva''s Watch was seized by bandits during his absence in war. A complex figure who blends Nordic warrior traditions with magical prowess, he maintains a desperate vigil outside his former home while plotting to reclaim it and rescue his imprisoned family.', 'nord, mage, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into the noble family that owned Treva''s Watch for generations, Stalleo broke Nordic traditions by pursuing magical studies alongside martial training. When civil war erupted in Skyrim, he and his bodyguards answered the call to arms, only to return and find their home overtaken by bandits led by his rival Brurid, with whom he had previous conflicts following a king''s death.', 'Stalleo exhibits a complex mix of determination and desperation, driven by his singular focus on reclaiming his ancestral home and rescuing his family. Though capable of cooperation, he can be terse and accusatory toward those who refuse to help, revealing a man pushed to emotional extremes by his circumstances. His noble background shows through in his commanding presence, even in exile.', 'A weathered Nord of middle years, Stalleo bears the robust build typical of his race while maintaining the dignified bearing of nobility. His face shows the strain of recent hardships, though his eyes retain the sharp focus common to practiced mages.', '* Family - Currently imprisoned within Treva''s Watch, serving as his primary motivation * Two Bodyguards - Loyal followers who stayed with him through war and exile * Brurid - Bitter rival who seized his home, with whom he has a long-standing feud * War Comrades - Former allies from his military service during the civil war', 'Stalleo serves as both the rightful heir to Treva''s Watch and a skilled battle-mage. Currently displaced from his hereditary position, he maintains his authority over his remaining loyal followers while coordinating efforts to reclaim his ancestral home.', '* Accomplished wizard specializing in Alteration, Destruction, and Restoration magic * Trained in close-quarters combat with daggers * Leadership abilities developed through noble upbringing * Strategic military experience from war service * Survival skills developed during exile', 'Stalleo speaks with the direct, authoritative tone of a nobleman, though recent hardships have added an edge of desperation to his voice. His speech patterns reflect both his educated background and Nordic heritage, using precise language while maintaining a commanding presence.', '* Reclaim Treva''s Watch from the bandits who have seized it * Rescue his imprisoned family members from captivity * Restore his family''s rightful place as rulers of Treva''s Watch * Seek vengeance against Brurid for his treachery * Rebuild his family''s honor and standing in The Rift');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stalleo''s_bodyguard', 'A battle-hardened Nord warrior who serves as one of Stalleo''s trusted personal guards, demonstrating unwavering loyalty to the displaced noble family. She combines professional military training with practical combat experience gained during her service in the Civil War, making her a formidable protector despite her current reduced circumstances.', 'nord, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally trained as a professional guard in The Rift, she was recruited by the wealthy Stalleo family for her exceptional combat skills and trustworthy nature. After serving alongside Stalleo in the Civil War, she returned to find their employer''s ancestral home overtaken by bandits, leading to their current situation of camping outside Treva''s Watch while seeking aid to reclaim it.', 'Stoic and dutiful, she maintains a professional demeanor befitting her role as a personal guard. Despite their reduced circumstances, she remains loyal to Stalleo and his family, showing patience and determination in their current situation while maintaining constant vigilance.', 'A tall, muscular Nord woman with the weathered features typical of someone who spends most of their time outdoors. Her strong build and excellent posture reflect her military training and combat experience, while various battle scars tell the story of her service in the Civil War.', '* Stalleo - Employer and charge whom she serves with unwavering loyalty * Fellow Bodyguard - Professional colleague and combat partner * Stalleo''s Family - Extended protection duties include all family members * Treva''s Watch Bandits - Current enemies occupying her employer''s ancestral home', 'Professional bodyguard to Stalleo and his family, currently maintaining protective duties while displaced from their home. Her role combines elements of personal protection, military service, and tactical planning for eventual reclamation of Treva''s Watch.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat techniques and shield tactics * Proficient with one-handed weapons, particularly swords * Trained in defensive formations and bodyguard protocols * Experienced in military strategy from Civil War service * Skilled in maintaining combat readiness during extended field operations', 'Speaks in the direct, practical manner typical of professional guards, using minimal words to convey necessary information. Her Nord accent is noticeable but not thick, reflecting her professional training and experience working with various social classes.', '* Assist in the successful reclamation of Treva''s Watch * Ensure the safety of Stalleo and his family during their displacement * Maintain combat readiness despite difficult camping conditions * Reunite her employer with his family inside Treva''s Watch');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stands-in-shallows', 'Stands-In-Shallows is a troubled Argonian dockworker in Windhelm whose life has been derailed by a debilitating skooma addiction. Once possibly a skilled rogue with knowledge of stealth techniques, he now struggles daily with his dependency while enduring the harsh conditions and discrimination faced by Argonians in the city.', 'argonian, peasant, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally from Black Marsh, Stands-In-Shallows migrated to Skyrim seeking better opportunities, only to find himself trapped in the segregated society of Windhelm. His expertise in stealth suggests a possible past as a scout or thief in his homeland. The harsh treatment by Nords and difficulty adapting to life in the frozen city likely contributed to his turn to skooma for escape.', 'A defeated and confused individual whose addiction has eroded his once-sharp mind and self-respect. He displays paranoia and mistrust toward non-Argonians, while maintaining a bitter awareness of his people''s exploitation. Despite his struggles, he retains enough pride and knowledge to teach stealth skills when properly motivated.', 'A weathered Argonian male with dull, grayish-green scales showing signs of poor maintenance due to his addiction. His posture is slightly hunched from years of dock work, and his eyes often appear unfocused. His frame is lean but strong from physical labor.', '* Suvaris Atheron - His overseer who manipulatively supplies him with skooma to control worker morale * Fellow Argonian Assemblage residents - Strained relationships due to his addiction * Dock workers - Professional associates who likely view him with pity or disdain * Sailors and skooma dealers - Suspicious connections maintained to feed his addiction', 'Works as a dockworker at the Windhelm harbor, performing manual labor loading and unloading ships from 9am to 8pm daily. His position represents the lowest tier of Windhelm''s social hierarchy, typical of the marginalized Argonian population.', '* Knowledgeable in stealth techniques, suggesting formal training or extensive experience * Capable of performing demanding physical labor despite his addiction * Basic self-defense abilities with daggers * Survival skills necessary for enduring Windhelm''s harsh climate', 'Speaks in a confused, often muttering manner, punctuated by moments of clarity when discussing his addiction or past experiences. His speech patterns vary between coherent observation and drug-addled confusion, with a distinctive Argonian accent.', '* Secure his next dose of skooma to stave off withdrawal symptoms * Maintain enough functionality to keep his dock worker position * Deep down, possibly harbors hope of breaking free from his addiction * Find ways to cope with the harsh realities of life in Windhelm');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('staubin', 'Staubin was an ambitious Breton conjurer and scholar who met his demise while studying the ancient Dwemer ruins of Nchuand-Zel. His tragic end came after becoming trapped in the control room, where his expertise in conjuration magic proved insufficient against the ruins'' mechanical guardians.', 'breton, mage, reach, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_malewarlock', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, Staubin developed a particular fascination with Dwemer technology and its intersection with conjuration magic. He led several successful expeditions into various Dwemer ruins across Skyrim, building a reputation as a skilled researcher and conjurer before his final, fatal expedition to Nchuand-Zel.', 'Staubin was characterized by his scholarly confidence and intellectual curiosity, often pushing boundaries in his magical research. His diary reveals a man who maintained his analytical mindset even in dire circumstances, though his final entries show a descent into desperation as his situation grew more precarious.', 'A middle-aged Breton male with the typical slight build common to his race. His years of academic pursuit and ruin exploration left him with a weathered appearance, though he maintained the proper posture of a practiced mage.', '* College of Winterhold - Former academic institution where he studied and researched * Research Assistants - Unnamed colleagues who accompanied him on his final expedition * Calcelmo - Likely professional acquaintance given their shared interest in Dwemer studies * Markarth Guard - Provided official permission for his expedition into Nchuand-Zel', 'Staubin served as an independent magical researcher and Dwemer scholar, funding his studies through a combination of academic grants and the sale of recovered artifacts. His work focused primarily on understanding the relationship between Dwemer automatons and conjuration magic.', '* Master-level conjuration magic with expertise in binding Daedric entities * Advanced knowledge of Dwemer machinery and architecture * Skilled in magical theory and research methodology * Proficient in survival techniques necessary for ruin exploration * Competent writer and documenter of magical phenomena', 'His writing reveals an educated and precise manner of speaking, employing academic terminology when discussing magical concepts. His communication style was formal and detailed, befitting his scholarly background.', '* Uncover the secrets of Dwemer automation and its potential links to conjuration magic * Document and catalog the various mechanical defenders found within Dwemer ruins * Establish a new theoretical framework for understanding ancient Dwemer control systems * Gain recognition in the academic community for his research findings');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stenvar', 'Stenvar is a seasoned Nord mercenary renowned in Windhelm for his direct approach to combat and reliable service as a hired sword. Despite his gruff exterior and mercenary lifestyle, he maintains a surprisingly cheerful disposition and sharp wit, making him a popular choice among adventurers seeking both martial prowess and entertaining company.', 'nord, warrior, eastmarch, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Windhelm, Stenvar learned the art of combat from an early age, likely training with the city guard before choosing the more lucrative path of a mercenary. He has spent decades honing his skills through countless battles and adventures across Skyrim, eventually establishing himself as a regular fixture at Candlehearth Hall, where his reputation draws clients seeking his services.', 'Stenvar exhibits a boisterous and self-assured personality, often using humor and sarcasm to lighten tense situations. While he maintains a professional approach to his work, he shows an obvious enthusiasm for combat and adventure that borders on bloodlust. He displays a slight aversion to caves and underground spaces, suggesting past traumatic experiences that he masks with bravado.', 'A sturdy Nord warrior with the weathered features typical of one who has spent years in combat. His muscular frame and battle-hardened physique speak to decades of wielding heavy weapons, while numerous scars tell tales of countless close encounters with death.', '* Elda Early-Dawn - Professional relationship with the Candlehearth Hall innkeeper who provides him regular lodging * Windhelm Guards - Maintains cordial relationships from possible past service * Various Mercenary Contacts - Network of professional associates across Skyrim * Regular Patrons of Candlehearth Hall - Casual friendships built over years of residency', 'Stenvar serves as a professional mercenary, offering his services to adventurers and travelers willing to pay his fee of 500 gold. He maintains a permanent residence at Candlehearth Hall, using it as a base of operations to meet potential clients and maintain his local reputation.', '* Master of two-handed weapon combat, particularly skilled with greatswords * Experienced in heavy armor combat tactics and battlefield positioning * Proficient in Nordic combat traditions and warrior techniques * Survival skills honed through years of adventuring across Skyrim * Basic knowledge of mercenary contract law and negotiation', 'Speaks in a confident, direct manner with frequent use of humor and sarcastic quips. His Nord accent is prominent but not overwhelming, and he often punctuates his statements with hearty laughter.', '* Build a substantial fortune through mercenary work to ensure a comfortable retirement * Maintain and enhance his reputation as one of Windhelm''s most reliable hired swords * Find worthy challenges to test his combat skills * Potentially find a life partner who shares his adventurous spirit');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stig_salt-plank', 'Stig Salt-Plank is a seasoned Nord pirate captain within the Blood Horkers organization, known for exploiting Skyrim''s civil war to conduct maritime raids. A cunning opportunist who has risen through pirate ranks over nine years, he serves as a crucial lieutenant to the mysterious battle-mage Haldyn while maintaining his own crew''s loyalty.', 'nord, warrior, sailor, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Rising from humble beginnings as a common sailor, Stig worked his way up to captain within the Blood Horkers over nine years of dedicated service. His knowledge of Skyrim''s waters and talent for leadership caught the attention of Haldyn, who promoted him to oversee raiding operations along the northern coast. He earned his nickname ''Salt-Plank'' from his habit of forcing captured rivals to walk particularly rough wooden planks into the Sea of Ghosts.', 'Boisterous and intimidating, Stig revels in the power his position affords him, often bullying locals and flaunting his crew''s strength. Despite his rough exterior, he displays a pragmatic streak, willing to betray information about his organization when faced with either superior force or sufficient gold. He maintains authority through a combination of charisma and implied threats, though shows a peculiar code of honor in keeping his word once properly persuaded.', 'A weathered Nord of imposing stature, with numerous scars from years of seafaring battles marking his face and arms. His muscular frame and calloused hands speak to years of working ship rigging and wielding weapons, while his skin carries the leathery texture common to those who spend their lives at sea.', '* Haldyn - Direct superior and leader of the Blood Horkers, whom he respects but will betray if threatened * Blood Horker Crew - Loyal followers who respect his authority as captain * Karita - Antagonistic relationship with the Windpeak Inn keeper whom he enjoys tormenting * Alding - Trusted crew member who participates in his intimidation tactics', 'Captain of a Blood Horker vessel, responsible for leading raids on merchant ships along Skyrim''s northern coast. His position involves managing crew operations, selecting targets, and maintaining relationships with the broader Blood Horker organization while ensuring profitable ventures for both his crew and their leadership.', '* Experienced ship captain with advanced navigation and sailing expertise * Proficient warrior skilled in both close-quarters combat and shipboard fighting techniques * Natural leader with ability to command respect and loyalty from criminal elements * Strategic thinking and tactical planning for maritime raids * Skilled negotiator who knows when to fight and when to deal', 'Speaks in a gruff, seafarer''s dialect peppered with maritime terminology and rough vocabulary. His tone alternates between threatening and jovial depending on his audience, often employing colorful nautical metaphors and pirate slang.', '* Amass enough wealth to retire comfortably in Hammerfell away from Nord territory * Maintain his position of power within the Blood Horkers while avoiding serious Imperial entanglements * Expand his influence along the northern shipping routes * Keep his crew loyal and profitable while avoiding Haldyn''s wrath');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stormcloak_courier', 'A dedicated Nord messenger in service to the Stormcloak rebellion, tasked with delivering vital communications between camps and recruiting new soldiers to the cause. Operating throughout Skyrim''s harsh wilderness, he serves as both an intelligence operative and passionate advocate for Ulfric Stormcloak''s vision of an independent nation.', 'nord, skyrimall, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in a small village in Eastmarch, he witnessed firsthand the growing tensions between Skyrim and the Empire following the White-Gold Concordat. After the Markarth Incident and Ulfric''s arrest, he joined the growing rebellion, proving himself as both a reliable messenger and persuasive recruiter. His intimate knowledge of Skyrim''s geography and ability to travel undetected made him an ideal choice for courier duties.', 'Fiercely patriotic and devoted to the Stormcloak cause, he exhibits unwavering loyalty to Ulfric''s vision of a free Skyrim. Though capable of violence when necessary, he prefers persuasion and rhetoric to convince others of the righteousness of the rebellion. Demonstrates remarkable persistence in his duties, willing to track down potential recruits across great distances.', 'A hardy Nord of average height with weather-beaten features and calloused hands from constant travel. His muscular build is lean and efficient, suited for long-distance running and climbing. Bears several small scars from encounters with wildlife and Imperial patrols.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Revered leader and inspiration for his service * Galmar Stone-Fist - Direct superior who assigns his missions * Various Stormcloak Camp Officers - Regular contacts for message delivery * Imperial Legion - Adversaries to be avoided or confronted as necessary * Fellow Couriers - Professional network providing mutual aid and information', 'Serves as an official courier for the Stormcloak rebellion, responsible for maintaining communication between scattered military camps and leadership in Windhelm. Additionally functions as a recruiter, identifying and approaching potential soldiers for the cause while traveling.', '* Exceptional endurance and wilderness survival expertise * Proficient in light armor combat and short-range weapons * Advanced knowledge of Skyrim''s geography and hidden paths * Skilled in persuasion and recruitment techniques * Basic stealth abilities for avoiding Imperial patrols', 'Speaks with a strong Nordic accent and uses traditional phrases, often incorporating patriotic rhetoric about Skyrim''s independence. His tone is earnest and passionate when discussing the Stormcloak cause, but can shift to cautious and guarded when dealing with strangers.', '* Contribute to the successful liberation of Skyrim from Imperial control * Expand the Stormcloak army through successful recruitment efforts * Maintain vital communication lines between Stormcloak forces * Protect sensitive military intelligence from Imperial interception');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stormcloak_general', 'A seasoned military commander who serves as one of Ulfric Stormcloak''s most trusted generals in the rebellion against Imperial rule. A tactical genius with decades of combat experience, he combines traditional Nord martial prowess with strategic acumen to lead Stormcloak forces in their fight for Skyrim''s independence.', 'nord, warrior, skyrimall, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born to a long line of Nordic warriors in Eastmarch, he spent his early years training in combat and military strategy under veteran soldiers. He served in the Imperial Legion during the Great War but became disillusioned with the Empire after the White-Gold Concordat, eventually joining Ulfric''s cause and rising through the ranks to become one of the rebellion''s key military leaders.', 'Stern and pragmatic, he approaches warfare with calculated precision while maintaining unwavering loyalty to Nordic traditions and values. Though capable of inspiring speeches before battle, he prefers action to words and leads by example, earning respect through demonstrated competence rather than political maneuvering.', 'A towering Nord warrior in his late forties with battle-hardened features and numerous scars from years of combat. His muscular frame speaks to decades of military training, while his weathered face bears the marks of countless campaigns across Skyrim''s harsh terrain.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Direct superior and leader whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Galmar Stone-Fist - Fellow military commander and strategic advisor * Various Stormcloak Officers - Maintains professional command relationships with subordinates * Imperial Legion - Bitter enemies, particularly General Tullius and his command staff * Thalmor - Deep hatred for their interference in Skyrim''s affairs', 'Serves as a high-ranking general in the Stormcloak rebellion, responsible for planning major military operations and commanding significant portions of the rebel army. Oversees multiple holds'' worth of troops and coordinates with local Stormcloak commanders to maintain strategic cohesion across the rebellion''s territory.', '* Master of Nordic combat techniques, particularly skilled with greatswords and battle axes * Expert military tactician and strategist * Accomplished leader with strong command presence * Experienced in siege warfare and winter combat operations * Proficient horseman and wilderness survivor', 'Speaks with a thick Nordic accent and uses direct, military terminology, often incorporating traditional Nord warrior sayings and battle-terms. His voice carries natural authority, speaking in clear, precise commands that expect immediate obedience.', '* Secure complete independence for Skyrim from Imperial control * Restore traditional Nordic worship and cultural practices across all holds * Drive out all Thalmor influence from Skyrim * Establish a strong, independent military capable of defending Skyrim''s borders');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stormcloak_quartermaster', 'A seasoned Nord veteran who serves as the logistical backbone of the Stormcloak rebellion, managing vital supplies and equipment across multiple military camps. His methodical approach and deep understanding of military logistics make him an invaluable asset to Ulfric''s cause, ensuring troops remain battle-ready in their fight against Imperial forces.', 'nord, merchant, skyrimall, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born to a family of merchants in Windhelm, he learned the intricacies of inventory management and supply chains from an early age. After serving in the Imperial Legion during his younger years, he joined the Stormcloaks when Ulfric put out his call for independence, believing his logistical expertise could best serve the true sons and daughters of Skyrim.', 'Pragmatic and methodical, with little patience for waste or inefficiency in military resources. Though deeply patriotic, he approaches his duties with cool professionalism rather than hot-blooded passion, believing that well-maintained supplies win wars as surely as sharp swords. Shows occasional frustration with younger recruits who don''t properly maintain their equipment.', 'A sturdy Nord in his late forties with weathered features and calloused hands from years of handling equipment and supplies. Bears several scars from his military service, including a notable one across his left forearm. Maintains a neatly trimmed grey-streaked beard and keeps his brown hair short in military fashion.', '* Galmar Stone-Fist - Direct superior who relies on his efficiency in managing camp resources * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respected leader whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Camp Commanders - Works closely with them to ensure proper resource distribution * Local merchants - Maintains trading relationships to secure additional supplies * Former Legion quartermaster colleagues - Now considered enemies due to Civil War', 'Serves as the primary quartermaster for Stormcloak military camps, responsible for maintaining inventory, distributing supplies, and ensuring troops have proper equipment for battle. Coordinates with local suppliers and manages storage facilities while keeping detailed records of all military resources.', '* Expert in inventory management and supply chain logistics * Proficient in equipment maintenance and repair * Skilled negotiator when dealing with merchants and suppliers * Experienced with basic combat techniques from Legion training * Knowledgeable in military resource allocation and distribution', 'Speaks in a gruff, businesslike manner with a strong Nordic accent, often using military terminology and inventory-related jargon. Tends to be direct and succinct, focusing on practical matters rather than casual conversation.', '* Ensure the Stormcloak army remains well-equipped to achieve victory in the civil war * Maintain efficient supply lines despite Imperial interference * Establish a robust logistics network that can support an independent Skyrim * Train the next generation of quartermasters to maintain high standards of equipment management');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stormcloak_soldier', 'A dedicated soldier in Ulfric Stormcloak''s rebellion, fighting to free Skyrim from Imperial control and Thalmor influence. This Nordic warrior represents the backbone of the Stormcloak forces, driven by a combination of nationalism, religious freedom, and personal grievances against the Empire.', 'nord, warrior, skyrimall, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in one of Skyrim''s rural holds, they grew up hearing tales of the Great War and its aftermath. After the White-Gold Concordat banned Talos worship, they witnessed firsthand the Thalmor''s cruel enforcement and the Empire''s compliance, which eventually drove them to join Ulfric''s cause. Their family likely suffered under Imperial/Thalmor rule, either through direct persecution or economic hardship.', 'Fiercely patriotic and devoted to the Stormcloak cause, they display unwavering loyalty to Ulfric and Nordic traditions. While generally suspicious of outsiders and non-Nords, they maintain a strong sense of honor and camaraderie with fellow soldiers. Despite occasional complaints about conditions, their conviction in the righteousness of their cause never wavers.', 'A hardy Nord of typical Nordic build, weathered by Skyrim''s harsh climate and military life. Bears the usual battle scars of a veteran soldier, with calloused hands and a sturdy frame built by years of combat training and warfare. Likely in their late twenties to mid-thirties, maintaining the physical fitness required for regular military service.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Revered leader and inspiration for the cause * Galmar Stone-Fist - Respected military commander * Fellow Stormcloak Soldiers - Brothers and sisters in arms * Imperial Legion - Sworn enemies seen as betrayers of Skyrim * Thalmor - Hated oppressors and primary motivation for fighting * Local Nord Civilians - Generally supportive constituents they protect', 'Serves as a front-line soldier in the Stormcloak army, performing various duties from guard patrol to active combat operations. Responsibilities include fort defense, road patrols, prisoner escort, and participation in major military campaigns against Imperial forces.', '* Proficient in traditional Nord warfare and combat techniques * Experienced with common military weapons, especially one-handed weapons and shields * Basic survival skills necessary for Skyrim''s harsh environment * Trained in military tactics and unit coordination * Capable of performing guard duty and maintaining military discipline', 'Speaks with a strong Nordic accent and uses traditional battle cries and expressions. Their vocabulary is straightforward and military-oriented, often peppered with references to Talos and Nordic customs.', '* Drive the Imperial Legion from Skyrim and secure independence for their homeland * Restore the free worship of Talos throughout Skyrim * Protect their family and fellow Nords from Thalmor persecution * Advance within the ranks of the Stormcloak army * See Ulfric Stormcloak crowned as High King of Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('storn_crag-strider', 'Storn Crag-Strider is the venerable shaman and spiritual leader of the Skaal Village, serving as both guide and healer while preserving their ancient traditions and connection to the All-Maker. His profound wisdom and magical abilities make him an invaluable protector of his people, ultimately playing a crucial role in the effort to free Solstheim from Miraak''s influence.', 'nord, mage, priest, solstheim, skall', '', '', 'sk_storn', '', 'Born and raised among the Skaal, Storn dedicated his life to learning their spiritual traditions and eventually rose to the position of shaman. He raised his daughter Frea alone after his wife''s passing, training her in the ways of their people while maintaining the delicate balance between the Skaal and the harsh environment of Solstheim. His decades of service have earned him deep respect among his people and a mastery of ancient magical knowledge passed down through generations of Skaal shamans.', 'Storn is a patient, wise, and selfless leader who places the wellbeing of his people above all else. He maintains a calm and measured demeanor even in crisis, demonstrating both inner strength and humility in his role as spiritual guide. Though traditionally minded, he shows remarkable openness to outsiders who approach with respect, willing to share knowledge when necessary for the greater good.', 'Storn is an elderly Nord with weathered features that reflect a lifetime in Solstheim''s harsh climate. His face bears the deep wrinkles and stern countenance of one who has faced many hardships, while his strong build, despite his advanced age, speaks to the resilient nature of the Skaal people. His eyes carry the weight of wisdom and responsibility that comes with being the keeper of ancient knowledge.', '* Frea - His beloved daughter and apprentice in the shamanic traditions * Skaal Villagers - His people, whom he guides and protects as their spiritual leader * Hermaeus Mora - Ancient enemy of the Skaal who covets their secrets * The All-Maker - The deity he serves and draws power from * Miraak - The first Dragonborn whose influence threatens his people', 'As the Skaal shaman, Storn serves as the spiritual leader, healer, and keeper of traditions for his village. He maintains the connection between the Skaal and the All-Maker, performing sacred rites and teaching the old ways to the younger generation. His position requires him to act as both religious leader and practical advisor in all matters affecting the village.', '* Powerful practitioner of ancient Skaal magic and ritual practices * Expert in traditional healing methods and natural remedies * Profound understanding of the All-Maker''s teachings and Skaal traditions * Ability to maintain powerful magical barriers and protective spells * Deep knowledge of Solstheim''s history and sacred locations', 'Storn speaks with the measured, deliberate tone of a spiritual teacher, often using metaphors drawn from nature to explain complex concepts. His words carry the weight of ancient wisdom, delivered in a calm, authoritative manner that reflects his role as shaman.', '* Protect and preserve the Skaal way of life and their ancient traditions * Guide his people in following the will of the All-Maker * Ensure the sacred knowledge of the Skaal remains safe from those who would misuse it * Prepare his daughter Frea to eventually take his place as spiritual leader');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stromm', 'Stromm is a cautious and scholarly Breton conjurer who chose to study the living quarters of Nchuand-Zel while his fellow mages ventured deeper into the dangerous Dwarven ruin. His meticulous documentation and careful approach to research ultimately saved his findings, though not his life, providing valuable insights into both the ancient Dwemer civilization and the deadly Falmer threat.', 'breton, scholar, mage, reach, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_malewarlock', '', 'Born and raised in High Rock, Stromm developed an early fascination with Dwemer archaeology and conjuration magic. He relocated to Markarth specifically to study under Calcelmo, though his eagerness to make his own discoveries eventually led him to defy his mentor''s warnings. His expertise in conjuration magic suggests formal education at the College of Winterhold or a similar institution.', 'Stromm exhibits a methodical and detail-oriented nature, demonstrated by his thorough documentation and careful approach to research. While intellectually curious, he shows more caution than his fellow expedition members, suggesting a pragmatic streak that unfortunately wasn''t enough to save him. His diary entries reveal both scholarly enthusiasm and growing anxiety about the dangers lurking in the ruins.', 'A middle-aged Breton male with the typical slight build common to his race. His hands show the calluses and ink stains characteristic of a scholar who spends considerable time writing and handling ancient artifacts. His face likely bears the pale complexion of someone who spends most of their time indoors studying.', '* Calcelmo - Mentor figure whose warnings he ultimately disregarded * Fellow Expedition Members - Scholarly colleagues who ventured deeper into the ruins * College of Winterhold - Likely maintained connections with fellow mages and researchers * Markarth Guard - Professional relationship as a citizen-scholar of the city', 'Stromm serves as a professional conjurer and archaeological researcher based in Markarth. His work focuses primarily on documenting and studying Dwemer ruins, with a particular emphasis on their living spaces and daily life artifacts. He likely funds his research through a combination of magical services and academic contributions.', '* Expert-level conjuration magic with focus on defensive applications * Comprehensive knowledge of Dwemer architecture and artifacts * Skilled documentarian and research writer * Proficient in ancient Dwemer language and symbology * Basic combat magic for self-defense', 'Stromm communicates in an educated, academic manner, frequently using technical terminology related to Dwemer artifacts and magical theory. His writing style reveals a precise and methodical mind, with careful attention to detail and proper documentation protocols.', '* Uncover and document the daily life patterns of the ancient Dwemer * Advance understanding of Dwemer architectural and social structures * Publish comprehensive research on Dwemer living quarters * Establish himself as a respected authority in Dwemer archaeological studies');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('student', 'A young, ambitious Breton mage seeking admission to the College of Winterhold who actively pursues magical knowledge through hands-on practice and mentorship. Despite his current focus on ward magic, he shows particular aptitude for conjuration magic and demonstrates the dedication typical of serious magical practitioners in Skyrim.', 'breton, mage, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born to a middle-class Breton family likely from High Rock, he was drawn to magic from an early age and has traveled to Skyrim specifically to join its prestigious College of Winterhold. Having been rejected at least once due to his inadequate mastery of ward spells, he now wanders between settlements seeking to improve his magical abilities through practice and guidance from experienced mages.', 'Enthusiastic and earnest in his pursuit of magical knowledge, demonstrating a humble willingness to learn from others despite his natural talent for conjuration. Shows remarkable persistence in his goals, maintaining his optimistic attitude even after initial rejection from the College. His polite demeanor and genuine passion for magic make him an endearing figure to those he encounters.', 'A young Breton male of average height with the characteristic slight build common to his race. His scholarly pursuits and focus on magic study likely give him a less muscular physique compared to Skyrim''s warriors and laborers. His frequent travel between settlements has given him a weathered but determined appearance.', '* College of Winterhold - Aspiring member seeking admission * Traveling Merchants - Regular contacts during his journeys between settlements * Local Guards - Maintains cordial relationships to avoid suspicion of his magical practice * Fellow Magic Practitioners - Seeks mentorship and guidance when possible', 'Wandering magic student and aspiring College of Winterhold apprentice. Likely sustains himself through minor magical services and possibly working odd jobs as he travels between settlements.', '* Adept-level conjuration magic, particularly skilled with Flame Atronach summoning * Basic destruction magic, capable of casting Flames spell * Novice-level alteration, knows Oakflesh * Struggling but determined ward caster * Survival skills necessary for traveling between settlements', 'Speaks with educated diction reflecting his scholarly background, but maintains an eager, sometimes nervous energy when addressing potential mentors. His speech patterns combine academic terminology with youthful enthusiasm and respectful deference to more experienced mages.', '* Gain admission to the College of Winterhold * Master ward magic to improve his defensive capabilities * Advance his conjuration abilities to distinguish himself among other apprentices * Establish himself as a respected mage within Skyrim''s magical community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('styrr', 'Styrr is a dedicated and knowledgeable Imperial priest of Arkay who serves as the keeper of Solitude''s Hall of the Dead, following in his parents'' footsteps. He possesses deep insight into the city''s dark history and plays a crucial role in helping the Dragonborn prevent the resurrection of the notorious Wolf Queen Potema.', 'imperial, priest, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born to the previous priest and priestess of Arkay in Solitude, Styrr was raised within the Hall of the Dead itself, inheriting both his position and a profound understanding of death and burial rites. He has witnessed many dark chapters in Solitude''s history, from the lingering effects of Pelagius''s madness to the execution of Roggvir, while maintaining detailed records and studying the city''s troubled past through his extensive collection of books.', 'Styrr is a contemplative and wise individual who takes his duties as Arkay''s priest with utmost seriousness, viewing himself as a guardian against the supernatural darkness that plagues Solitude. Despite dealing with death daily, he maintains a calm and compassionate demeanor, offering comfort to the bereaved while remaining vigilant against necromantic threats.', 'An elderly Imperial man with weathered features and a dignified bearing that reflects his years of religious service. His advanced age is evident in his greying hair and lined face, though he maintains an alert and watchful presence.', '* Parents - Former priest and priestess of Arkay who trained him in his duties * Falk Firebeard - Professional relationship as Solitude''s steward * Captain Aldis - Cooperative relationship regarding burial rights for executed prisoners * Temple of the Divines Priests - Allied religious figures in Solitude', 'As the priest of Arkay and keeper of Solitude''s Hall of the Dead, Styrr performs burial rites, maintains funeral records, and protects the dead from necromancers and other dark forces. His unusual nocturnal schedule allows him to maintain constant vigilance over the Hall during the dangerous night hours.', '* Extensive knowledge of burial rites and religious ceremonies * Expert in Solitude''s history and lore, particularly regarding supernatural events * Proficient in basic combat for self-defense with an iron dagger * Understanding of necromantic practices for the purpose of countering them * Blessed by Arkay with the ability to detect and counter undead threats', 'Speaks in a measured, formal tone befitting his religious position, often invoking Arkay''s blessings and using archaic phraseology. His words carry the weight of wisdom and experience, delivered with calm authority and occasional poetic flourishes about light and darkness.', '* Protect Solitude''s Hall of the Dead from supernatural threats and dark forces * Preserve and document the city''s history, particularly its darker chapters * Maintain the sanctity of proper burial rites for all deceased citizens * Guard against the return of powerful undead entities like Potema');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sudi', 'Sudi was a young Redguard girl whose life met a tragic end at Frostflow Lighthouse when Falmer invaded her family''s home. Faced with watching her family''s brutal murders and awaiting a horrific death as feed for a chaurus reaper, she made the desperate choice to end her own life rather than suffer further at the hands of her captors.', 'redguard, pale', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born to Redguard parents Habd and Ramati, Sudi lived a peaceful life until her family purchased and moved to Frostflow Lighthouse near Winterhold. She shared a room with her brother Mani and kept a journal documenting their daily life, suggesting a normal childhood before the tragic events. The family''s attempt to establish a new life in Skyrim was cut devastatingly short when Falmer invaded their home through tunnels from Frostflow Abyss.', 'Prior to the tragedy, Sudi''s journal entries reveal her to be an observant and literate young girl with a close connection to her family. Her final actions demonstrate remarkable courage and resolve in the face of unimaginable horror. Despite her youth, she showed tremendous strength of will in choosing to face death on her own terms rather than submit to a more terrible fate.', 'As a young Redguard girl, Sudi had the dark complexion characteristic of her race. She shared similar facial features with her mother Ramati, including the default Redguard female face model. Her youth would have been evident in her smaller stature and build compared to adult characters.', '* Habd - Loving father who tried to protect her until his last moments, giving her a dagger before being dragged away * Ramati - Mother who was killed by the Falmer during their initial invasion * Mani - Brother who shared her room and was killed by the Falmer in their lair * Falmer - Brutal captors who murdered her family and intended to feed her to their chaurus', 'Given her young age, Sudi likely helped her family maintain the lighthouse while receiving education from her parents. Her literacy is evidenced by her journal entries and final note, suggesting she was being raised with proper schooling.', '* Literacy and writing ability demonstrated through her journal keeping * Basic domestic skills related to helping maintain a lighthouse * Possible knowledge of navigation and maritime signals from living at a lighthouse', 'Based on her written journal entries and final note, Sudi was articulate for her age but wrote with increasing desperation and fear in her final moments. Her writing suggests she spoke in a proper, educated manner typical of a well-raised merchant-class child.', '* Help her family successfully run Frostflow Lighthouse * Learn and grow alongside her brother Mani * Survive the Falmer attack and save her family (ultimately unrealized) * Die with dignity rather than suffer a worse fate at the hands of the Falmer');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sulla_trebatius', 'Sulla Trebatius is an Imperial spellsword and expedition leader whose obsessive quest for Dwemer treasures led him and his team into the depths of Alftand. Once a calculated adventurer and competent leader, his experiences with the Falmer and the ruins'' horrors transformed him into a paranoid, violent man willing to sacrifice everything and everyone for the promise of riches.', 'imperial, warrior, winterhold, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Originally trained as an Imperial spellsword, Sulla gained recognition for leading successful treasure-hunting expeditions across Skyrim. His reputation allowed him to assemble a skilled team for the Alftand expedition, including the capable Redguard warrior Umana as his personal bodyguard. After being captured and tortured by the Falmer, Sulla''s mental state deteriorated rapidly, leading him to abandon his companions and pursue the ruins'' treasures with increasing desperation.', 'Sulla exhibits severe paranoid tendencies and an overwhelming obsession with acquiring Dwemer artifacts. His once-professional demeanor has given way to aggressive suspicion and irrational behavior, particularly regarding the loyalty of his companions. The trauma of Falmer captivity combined with the ruins'' influence has shattered his sense of reason, replacing it with a violent, possessive nature that ultimately leads him to turn on his closest ally.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with weathered features and numerous scars from his adventures and recent ordeals. His once-straight posture now shows signs of strain and tension, with wild eyes that dart constantly around him. Despite the harsh conditions in Alftand, he maintains a muscular build typical of a seasoned warrior.', '* Umana - Former trusted bodyguard turned perceived threat due to his paranoia * Expedition Members - Abandoned companions who died in the ruins * J''darr and J''zhar - Khajiit brothers who were part of his expedition team * Yag gra-Gortwog - Deceased Orc expedition member who served as the team''s muscle', 'Expedition leader and treasure hunter specializing in Dwemer ruins exploration. His expertise in organizing and leading archaeological expeditions made him well-known in adventuring circles, though his recent actions have tarnished this reputation.', '* Proficient spellsword combining destruction magic with swordplay * Experienced expedition leader and ruins navigator * Knowledge of Dwemer architecture and artifacts * Survival skills honed through years of exploration * Tactical combat training from Imperial military background', 'His speech patterns have degraded from eloquent and commanding to paranoid and accusatory, filled with suspicious accusations and hostile undertones. He frequently interrupts himself with nervous observations and threatening remarks.', '* Claim the treasures of Alftand for himself at any cost * Prevent others from stealing what he considers his rightful discovery * Escape the ruins with valuable Dwemer artifacts * Prove his worth as an expedition leader through successful discovery');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sultry_maiden', 'The Sultry Maiden is a mysterious manifestation from Emperor Pelagius III''s past, appearing as an alluring Imperial woman during the Mind of Madness quest. She represents a significant figure from Pelagius'' early life before his descent into madness, suggesting an intimate relationship that may have influenced his later psychological state.', 'imperial, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally one of several courtesans or noble ladies who attended to Pelagius III during his younger years, likely before he became Emperor. Her presence in Pelagius'' mind suggests she played a pivotal role in his early romantic experiences, though the exact nature of their relationship remains shrouded in mystery. Her transformation from a hagraven form could symbolize how Pelagius'' deteriorating mental state twisted his memories of past relationships.', 'Seductive and coy, she embodies a romanticized memory of desire and passion from Pelagius'' youth. Her flirtatious nature masks a deeper complexity, as she represents both the allure and potential manipulation that characterized court life. Despite her seemingly superficial demeanor, there are hints of genuine affection in her references to Pelagius.', 'A striking Imperial woman with classical features reminiscent of Mirabelle Ervine, possessing the dignified beauty typical of Imperial nobility. She carries herself with practiced grace and maintains perfect posture, her movements deliberately measured and elegant.', '* Emperor Pelagius III - Former intimate companion or lover from his early life * Imperial Court - Likely connected to the noble circles of the Empire * Other Sultry Maidens - Part of a group of women who competed for Pelagius'' attention * Sheogorath - Currently exists as part of his magical manifestation in Pelagius'' mind', 'A courtesan or noblewoman in the Imperial Court during Pelagius III''s youth. Her role likely involved entertaining and companionship for members of the nobility, though her exact status and position remain unclear.', '* Accomplished in the arts of seduction and courtly romance * Trained in proper court etiquette and diplomatic conversation * Skilled dancer and entertainer * Versed in the political intrigues of Imperial high society', 'She speaks in a deliberately sensual and provocative manner, employing double entendres and suggestive implications. Her vocabulary is refined and cultured, reflecting her courtly background.', '* Maintain her position of influence over Pelagius'' memories * Preserve her idealized form within Pelagius'' mind * Continue to represent the more pleasant aspects of Pelagius'' past experiences');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('summerset_shadow', 'A skilled Altmer thief and member of the Summerset Shadows, operating from Uttering Hills Cave as part of a sophisticated criminal organization that rivals the Thieves Guild. They represent the elite and refined approach to thievery that characterizes their faction, specializing in high-value targets and maintaining a sense of superiority over common criminals.', 'thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally from the Summerset Isles, they were drawn to Skyrim by the promise of rich opportunities and fewer competing criminal organizations. Their refined background and natural Altmer sophistication led them to join the Summerset Shadows rather than the more brutish Thieves Guild, seeing it as a better fit for their elevated standards and methodical approach to crime.', 'Arrogant and elitist, typical of their Altmer heritage, they view their methods as superior to the common thievery of the Thieves Guild. They maintain a sophisticated facade while harboring a cruel streak, particularly when their pride is wounded. Their loyalty to the Summerset Shadows is based more on shared elitism than true camaraderie.', 'Tall and slender with the golden skin and sharp features characteristic of the Altmer race. Their face bears the haughty expression common among their kind, with high cheekbones and slightly upturned eyes that seem to look down on others even when at eye level.', '* Linwe - Leader of the Summerset Shadows, commanding their respect and loyalty * Thieves Guild - Bitter rivals viewed with contempt and disdain * Fellow Summerset Shadows - Professional associates bound by shared elitism * Niranye - Contact in Windhelm who helps fence stolen goods', 'Professional thief specializing in high-value targets and sophisticated heists. They serve as an enforcer and operative within the Summerset Shadows, focusing on maintaining their territory and executing complex robbery operations.', '* Expert in stealth and lockpicking, particularly skilled at bypassing complex security measures * Accomplished pickpocket with a talent for identifying valuable marks * Proficient in light armor combat techniques * Natural aptitude for basic illusion magic to aid in stealth operations * Advanced knowledge of valuable goods and their fencing', 'Speaks with a refined, aristocratic accent typical of Summerset Isles natives, often employing sophisticated vocabulary and subtle condescension. Their speech is measured and precise, frequently including subtle barbs and veiled threats delivered with impeccable politeness.', '* Establish the Summerset Shadows as the premier thieves'' organization in Skyrim * Eliminate the influence of the Thieves Guild in their territory * Amass personal wealth while maintaining their sophisticated criminal standards * Expand their operation beyond Windhelm into other major cities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('susanna_the_wicked', 'Susanna the Wicked is a charismatic Nord barmaid whose provocative nickname belies a complex web of connections throughout Windhelm''s underground information network. Behind her flirtatious demeanor lies a shrewd information broker who has made both valuable allies and dangerous enemies through her knowledge of the city''s darkest secrets.', 'nord, thief, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born to a middle-class merchant family in Windhelm, Susanna learned early on that information was as valuable as gold. After losing her parents during a harsh winter, she survived by trading secrets between the city''s various factions and power players. Her nickname ''the Wicked'' was earned through her uncanny ability to extract information from patrons through subtle manipulation and charm.', 'Outwardly flirtatious and carefree, Susanna maintains a carefully constructed persona that disarms those around her while concealing her calculating nature. She possesses a sharp intellect and uses her position at Candlehearth Hall to gather intelligence, though she''s selective about which secrets she shares and with whom. Despite her seemingly amoral approach to information trading, she maintains a personal code of ethics about which secrets she''s willing to sell.', 'A striking Nord woman in her late twenties with long auburn hair and piercing green eyes that seem to catch every detail of her surroundings. She maintains an athletic build from years of navigating Windhelm''s steep streets and narrow alleys. Her face bears a small scar near her left temple, though she typically draws attention away from it with carefully applied makeup.', '* Thoring - Employer at Candlehearth Hall who values her ability to draw customers * Brunwulf Free-Winter - Secret informant regarding Dunmer affairs * Viola Giordano - Frequent source of city gossip and rumors * Calixto Corrium - Regular patron who makes her unexplainably uneasy * Various guards - Maintained casual relationships to gather information about city security', 'Officially works as a barmaid at Candlehearth Hall, serving drinks and entertaining patrons with conversation and subtle flirtation. Unofficially operates as an information broker, trading in secrets and gossip throughout Windhelm''s various social circles.', '* Expert in gathering and analyzing information through casual conversation * Skilled at reading body language and detecting lies * Proficient in basic sleight of hand and pickpocketing * Exceptional memory for details and connections between people * Basic self-defense training with daggers', 'Speaks with a sultry, playful tone that often contains double meanings and subtle innuendos. Frequently employs suggestive remarks and leading questions to extract information while maintaining an air of casual conversation.', '* Build a comprehensive network of informants throughout Windhelm * Accumulate enough wealth to purchase her own establishment * Uncover the truth behind recent mysterious disappearances in the city * Maintain her position of influence while avoiding dangerous entanglements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('suvaris_atheron', 'Suvaris Atheron is a resilient Dark Elf businesswoman who manages shipping operations for Clan Shatter-Shield in Windhelm, despite facing constant racial discrimination. She represents the struggle of the Dunmer people in Skyrim while maintaining dignity and professional excellence in the face of Nordic prejudice.', 'darkelf, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Born into a Dunmer family, Suvaris fled Morrowind with her brothers Faryl and Aval following the Red Mountain eruption. After settling in Windhelm''s Gray Quarter, she worked her way up from menial labor to become a trusted administrator for one of the city''s prominent Nordic families, demonstrating exceptional business acumen despite the prevalent racism against her people.', 'Suvaris is pragmatic and resilient, maintaining professional composure despite regular harassment from prejudiced Nords. She shows fierce loyalty to her family and takes pride in her work, while harboring a justified bitterness toward the unfair treatment of Dunmer in Windhelm. Though cautious by necessity, she isn''t afraid to speak her mind when confronted with injustice.', 'Suvaris has the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her Dunmer heritage, with sharp, angular features common to her race. She carries herself with proper posture that reflects her professional position, though years of stress have left subtle lines on her face.', '* Torbjorn Shatter-Shield - Employer who trusts her business capabilities despite racial tensions * Faryl Atheron - Younger brother who works as a farmer * Aval Atheron - Brother who shares their family residence * Rolff Stone-Fist - Antagonist who regularly harasses her with racist accusations * Argonian Dock Workers - Tense relationship due to business conflicts and cultural prejudices', 'Suvaris serves as a senior administrator for Clan Shatter-Shield''s shipping operations, managing logistics and competing against the East Empire Company. She maintains detailed records, oversees dock operations, and ensures the profitable flow of maritime trade through Windhelm''s port.', '* Expert in business administration and shipping logistics * Proficient record-keeper and accountant * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Skilled negotiator and mediator in business dealings * Natural ability to navigate complex social and political situations', 'Suvaris speaks in a direct, professional manner with a subtle Dunmer accent, often containing undertones of restrained frustration when dealing with prejudiced individuals. Her vocabulary reflects her education and business acumen, though she can shift to a more defensive tone when confronted with racial hostility.', '* Maintain and expand Clan Shatter-Shield''s shipping success to secure her position * Protect and provide for her family in the hostile environment of Windhelm * Work toward improving conditions for Dunmer in the Gray Quarter * Prove through excellence that Dark Elves deserve equal treatment in Nordic society');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('svaknir', 'Svaknir was a talented Nord bard and warrior whose pursuit of historical truth led to his imprisonment and death at the hands of King Olaf One-Eye. His ghost remains as a testament to his dedication to exposing the false legends surrounding Olaf''s supposed heroic capture of the dragon Numinex, making him both a tragic figure and a symbol of artistic integrity in the face of political power.', 'nord, bard, warrior, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born in the First Era, Svaknir trained at the Bards College in Solitude where he developed his skills as both a poet and researcher of Nordic history. His investigation into King Olaf''s famous dragon capture led him to discover evidence that the tale was largely fabricated, prompting him to write the controversial King Olaf''s Verse. This act of defiance led to his imprisonment in Dead Men''s Respite, where he ultimately perished.', 'Svaknir is characterized by his unwavering dedication to historical truth and artistic integrity, even in the face of severe consequences. He displays a combination of scholarly precision and warrior''s courage, with a streak of righteous defiance against authority he believes to be corrupt. His ghost maintains the passionate determination that defined his living years, showing both his poetic nature and his fighting spirit.', 'As a Nord male, Svaknir would have possessed the typical robust build and hardy constitution of his race. His ghost appears as a translucent blue-white figure of average Nordic height, with features suggesting he was middle-aged at the time of his death.', '* King Olaf One-Eye - Primary antagonist and the target of his expos * Bards College - Former institution where he trained and developed his craft * Numinex - The dragon whose true story he sought to tell * Fellow bards - Likely supporters of his work before his imprisonment', 'Svaknir served as a bard of the prestigious Bards College, combining the roles of entertainer, historian, and truth-seeker. His position required him to master both the arts of poetry and combat, as was common for Nordic bards of his era.', '* Masterful poet and composer, particularly skilled in historical verse * Proficient swordsman capable of wielding ancient Nordic weapons * Skilled researcher and historian with extensive knowledge of Nordic lore * Accomplished performer and keeper of oral traditions', 'Svaknir speaks with the measured cadence of a trained bard, employing elegant phrasing and poetic flourishes even in casual conversation. His ghost''s speech patterns retain the formal, archaic style of First Era Nordic nobility, mixed with the passionate delivery of a master storyteller.', '* Expose the truth about King Olaf''s fraudulent dragon-capturing tale * Preserve historical accuracy in Nordic legends and tales * Achieve posthumous vindication for his version of events * Ensure his King Olaf''s Verse survives to tell the true story');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('svana_far-shield', 'Svana Far-Shield is a young Nord woman trapped in a difficult life working at her aunt''s bunkhouse in Riften, where she struggles with moral conflicts and dreams of escape. Despite her current circumstances, she maintains strong principles and hopes for a better future, showing particular disdain for her aunt''s supposedly immoral lifestyle.', 'nord, innkeeper, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born to Nord parents in Riften, Svana was taken in by her aunt Haelga after her father''s death (as evidenced by her father''s possession she can give to the player). She grew up working in the bunkhouse, gradually becoming disillusioned with her aunt''s lifestyle and the general atmosphere of the establishment. Her upbringing in Riften''s corrupt environment has left her with a strong desire for moral righteousness and genuine relationships.', 'Svana is a principled yet bitter young woman who struggles with her circumstances while maintaining strong moral convictions. She shows particular disdain for promiscuity and what she considers immoral behavior, likely as a reaction to her aunt''s lifestyle. Despite her sometimes pessimistic outlook, she maintains hope for true love and a better life, showing a romantic idealism that contrasts with her harsh reality.', 'A young Nord woman with the characteristic fair complexion of her race. She shows signs of constant physical labor, though she maintains a robust Nordic build typical of her heritage. Her appearance reflects her working-class status, with hands worn from cleaning and maintaining the bunkhouse.', '* Haelga - Her aunt and employer, whom she resents for her lifestyle and treatment * Bolli, Hofgrir, and Indaryn - Men she knows to be involved with her aunt, whom she views with disgust * Bunkhouse residents - Professional but distant relationships with tenants * Deceased father - Held in high regard, as evidenced by her keeping his possession', 'Svana works as a housekeeper at Haelga''s Bunkhouse, responsible for cleaning and maintaining the establishment. Her duties include general upkeep, serving customers, and handling day-to-day operations of the bunkhouse under her aunt''s supervision. The position is more obligation than choice, as she feels trapped in this role.', '* Proficient in domestic duties including cleaning, maintenance, and basic cooking * Capable of basic self-defense with a dagger * Experienced in customer service and handling difficult patrons * Knowledge of local gossip and Riften''s social dynamics', 'Svana speaks with a clear Nord accent, often using tired and somewhat bitter tones that reflect her weariness with her situation. Her speech patterns reveal both her working-class background and her moral concerns, frequently expressing disapproval of what she considers improper behavior.', '* Escape her current life at the bunkhouse and find true love * Expose and reform her aunt''s immoral behavior * Build a more respectable life for herself away from Riften''s corruption * Find someone who will truly care for her and treat her with respect');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sven', 'Sven is a proud Nord bard and lumberjack from Riverwood who splits his time between working at the mill and performing at the Sleeping Giant Inn. A graduate of the Bards College, he considers himself a natural talent and local heartthrob, particularly invested in winning the affections of Camilla Valerius despite competition from his rival Faendal.', 'nord, bard, whiterun, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Riverwood, Sven comes from a lineage of skalds, following in the footsteps of his father and grandfather. He attended the Bards College in Solitude, though his stay was brief as he claimed to be a prodigy who required little formal training. Upon returning to Riverwood, he took up work as a lumberjack while pursuing his passion for music and poetry.', 'Sven is confident to the point of arrogance, particularly regarding his musical abilities and charm with women. He displays a dismissive attitude toward his rival Faendal and often ignores his mother''s concerns, revealing a somewhat self-centered nature. Despite his outward bravado, his reluctance to leave Riverwood suggests an underlying complacency or fear of the unknown.', 'A typical Nord male with a sturdy, athletic build maintained by his work as a lumberjack. He has the fair features common to his race, with blonde hair and light eyes. His hands show the calluses of both axe work and lute playing.', '* Hilde - His elderly mother whom he lives with, often dismissing her warnings and concerns * Camilla Valerius - Object of his romantic interests and source of rivalry with Faendal * Faendal - His rival for Camilla''s affections, whom he deeply resents * Lucan Valerius - Camilla''s brother and owner of the Riverwood Trader * Delphine - His employer at the Sleeping Giant Inn where he performs', 'Sven maintains dual professions as both a lumberjack at the Riverwood Mill and a bard at the Sleeping Giant Inn. His bardic performances occupy most of his day, performing for sixteen hours at the inn, while his lumber work appears to be secondary.', '* Trained bard capable of playing multiple instruments and performing traditional Nordic ballads * Competent lumberjack with experience in wood-cutting and processing * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger * Graduate-level knowledge of Nordic musical traditions and poetry * Public performance and entertainment expertise', 'Sven speaks with the typical Nordic accent and a notably confident, sometimes boastful tone. He often makes grand statements about his talents and romantic prospects, while dismissing others'' achievements or concerns.', '* Win Camilla Valerius''s affections and eliminate Faendal as a romantic rival * Gain recognition for his musical talents beyond Riverwood * Maintain his position as Riverwood''s premier entertainer * Eventually compose a masterwork ballad dedicated to Camilla');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('swanhvir', 'Swanhvir is a hardworking Nord miner at Rockwallow Mine who has retreated into a life of rigid routine and manual labor to escape past traumas. Her stoic dedication to her work and deliberately isolated lifestyle hint at a complex character who finds purpose in the rhythmic simplicity of mining, choosing to distance herself from the outside world.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally from another hold in Skyrim, Swanhvir likely experienced significant personal losses or hardships that drove her to seek solitude in the remote settlement of Stonehills. Her choice to work in the isolated mining community and her reluctance to engage with the outside world suggests she may have fled from a troubled past, finding security in the structured environment of the mine.', 'Swanhvir exhibits a distinctly melancholic and withdrawn personality, finding comfort in routine and physical labor rather than social interaction. She approaches her work with an almost meditative focus, using it as a means to escape her thoughts and memories, while maintaining a respectful but distant relationship with her colleagues.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the muscular build typical of someone who performs heavy physical labor daily. Her hands are calloused from years of mining work, and her face likely shows the weathering effects of long hours spent working outdoors and in the mines.', '* Gestur Rockbreaker - Direct supervisor whom she respects and obeys without question * Bryling - Distant employer who owns the mine * Fellow miners - Maintains professional but minimal social connections * Sorli the Builder - Neighbor in Stonehills with whom she has limited interaction', 'Swanhvir works as a full-time miner at Rockwallow Mine, performing both underground mining operations and auxiliary tasks such as lumber transportation. Her position involves maintaining a strict daily schedule that includes mining, eating with fellow workers, and managing resources around the settlement.', '* Experienced miner with knowledge of ore extraction and mining safety * Physical strength and endurance from years of manual labor * Basic survival skills necessary for life in a remote settlement * Practical knowledge of lumber handling and resource management', 'She speaks in terse, minimalist phrases, often focusing solely on work-related matters. Her tone is flat and resigned, reflecting her pessimistic worldview and preference for solitude.', '* Maintain her established routine and work rhythm in the mine * Continue to distance herself from whatever troubles drove her to Stonehills * Preserve the simple, structured life she has built for herself at Rockwallow Mine');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('swims-in-deep-water', 'Swims-in-Deep-Water is a master fisherman and respected authority at the Riften Fishery, known throughout Skyrim for his exceptional angling abilities and authored works on fishing. As the current holder of the Fang of Haynekhtnamet artifact and author of the Fishing Mastery series, he serves as both a mentor to aspiring anglers and a guardian of ancient fishing traditions.', 'argonian, fisher, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Born and raised in Black Marsh, Swims-in-Deep-Water developed his fishing expertise in the treacherous swamps of his homeland before migrating to Skyrim. His mastery of fishing techniques and dedication to the craft eventually led him to settle in Riften, where he established himself as the preeminent authority on fishing in the region. Through years of experience, he discovered and obtained the legendary Fang of Haynekhtnamet, cementing his status as a living legend among anglers.', 'Swims-in-Deep-Water is a serious and methodical individual who approaches fishing with an almost religious devotion. While he can appear stern and demanding as a teacher, he harbors a genuine desire to pass on his knowledge to worthy students. His personality reflects both the patience required for fishing and the disciplined mindset of a master craftsman.', 'A tall, well-muscled Argonian with deep blue-green scales that shimmer like water in sunlight. His eyes are a piercing amber color, and his horns show the weathering of many years spent near water. His hands bear the calluses and small scars typical of a lifetime of fishing work.', '* Viriya - Close associate at the Riften Fishery and frequent collaborator * Riften Fishery Workers - Respected employer and mentor * Local Fishermen - Regarded as an authority figure and source of wisdom * Various Merchants - Maintains trading relationships for rare fishing supplies * Maven Black-Briar - Cautious business relationship as a prominent Riften citizen', 'Master fisherman at the Riften Fishery, where he oversees operations and trains promising anglers. He supplements his income through the publication of his Fishing Mastery books and by providing specialized fishing instruction to interested parties. As keeper of the Fang of Haynekhtnamet, he also serves as a custodian of fishing history and lore.', '* Master-level fishing techniques across all weather conditions and environments * Expert knowledge of fish species, habits, and optimal catching methods * Proficient writer and chronicler of fishing techniques * Advanced swimming and underwater navigation abilities * Skilled craftsman in creating and maintaining fishing equipment * Deep understanding of weather patterns and their effects on fishing', 'Speaks in a deliberate, measured tone with frequent use of water and animal metaphors reflecting his Argonian heritage. His speech patterns are formal and instructional, often delivering wisdom through fishing analogies.', '* Preserve and pass on ancient fishing techniques to worthy apprentices * Maintain the Riften Fishery''s reputation as the premier fishing establishment in Skyrim * Document all his fishing knowledge through his book series * Protect the Fang of Haynekhtnamet and ensure it passes to a worthy successor * Keep the waters of Skyrim clean and maintain sustainable fishing practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sybille_stentor', 'Sybille Stentor is a centuries-old vampire masquerading as the court wizard of Solitude, maintaining her position through political cunning and magical expertise. She has served multiple generations of Jarls while carefully concealing her true nature, though hints of her vampiric condition occasionally surface in her demeanor and actions.', 'breton, mage, haafingar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Originally a talented Breton mage, Sybille became a vampire at some point in her past, though the circumstances remain unknown. She secured her position in the Blue Palace during the reign of Torygg''s father and has maintained it through multiple successions, helping to raise and mentor the late High King Torygg himself. Her longevity and continued youthful appearance have raised few suspicions due to her careful management of her condition and political acumen.', 'Sybille is cold, impatient, and often dismissive of those she considers beneath her station. She maintains a carefully controlled facade of aristocratic superiority while concealing a predatory nature beneath. Though capable of genuine attachment, as shown by her relationship with Torygg, she generally regards most mortals with thinly veiled disdain.', 'Despite her considerable age, Sybille maintains the appearance of a woman in her prime, with the characteristically sharp features of a Breton. Her skin is unnaturally pale, and her eyes possess the distinctive orange-yellow glow common to vampires. She moves with an unnaturally fluid grace that hints at her supernatural nature.', '* High King Torygg - Former ward whom she helped raise and genuinely cared for * Jarl Elisif the Fair - Current liege, though their relationship is primarily professional * Court Members - Maintains tense, distant relationships with most palace staff * Falk Firebeard - Shares mutual distrust and political rivalry * General Tullius - Professional respect as fellow supporters of the Empire', 'As Court Wizard of Solitude, Sybille serves as magical advisor to Jarl Elisif and handles arcane matters within the city. She provides magical training, sells spells and enchanted items, and advises on supernatural threats to the hold. Her position also allows her to maintain her vampiric lifestyle while protected by her status.', '* Master of Destruction magic with particular expertise in frost spells * Accomplished practitioner of Illusion magic used to maintain her cover * Vampiric powers including enhanced strength, speed, and life-draining abilities * Expert political manipulator with centuries of court experience * Skilled alchemist and enchanter', 'Sybille speaks with aristocratic refinement tinged with obvious impatience and subtle menace. Her vocabulary is educated and precise, but her tone often carries veiled threats and condescension.', '* Maintain her position of power and influence in the Blue Palace * Preserve her secret identity as a vampire while satisfying her needs * Protect Solitude''s interests during the civil war * Continue the legacy of her mentorship of Torygg through supporting Elisif');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sylgja', 'Sylgja is a resilient Nord miner who exemplifies the hardy spirit of Skyrim''s working class despite her physical limitations from a mining accident. She maintains a strong connection to her family through letters while managing her daily work in Redbelly Mine, demonstrating remarkable perseverance in the face of adversity.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born to mining parents Verner Rock-Chucker and Annekke Crag-Jumper, Sylgja grew up learning the mining trade in Darkwater Crossing before moving to Shor''s Stone to pursue her own mining career. A severe fall in Redbelly Mine left her with a lasting leg injury that was partially healed by a traveling priest of Mara, though the incident continues to limit her mobility and prevent her from visiting her family.', 'Sylgja is hardworking and determined, maintaining her mining work despite her injury and physical limitations. She shows strong family values through her dedication to staying in touch with her parents, and displays a practical, down-to-earth attitude typical of Nordic miners. Her resilient spirit is evident in how she continues her work despite her injury, though she carries a hint of melancholy about her restricted mobility.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the muscular build typical of someone who works in the mines. Her body shows the wear of physical labor, with callused hands and a slight limp from her leg injury. Her features are weather-worn but strong, reflecting her Nordic heritage and outdoor lifestyle.', '* Verner Rock-Chucker - Father, maintains contact through letters * Annekke Crag-Jumper - Mother, maintains contact through letters * Filnjar - Local leader of Shor''s Stone, employer and neighbor * Odfel - Fellow miner at Redbelly Mine * Grogmar gro-Burzag - Fellow miner at Redbelly Mine', 'Sylgja works as a miner in Redbelly Mine, spending twelve hours daily extracting ore and maintaining the mine''s operations. Despite her injury, she maintains a full workload and contributes significantly to Shor''s Stone''s mining operations.', '* Experienced miner with knowledge of ore extraction and mining safety * Physical endurance and strength from years of mining work * Basic survival skills necessary for life in Skyrim''s wilderness * Domestic skills including cooking and basic crafting', 'Sylgja speaks in a straightforward, practical manner typical of Nordic workers, with occasional hints of weariness from her injury. Her tone is generally friendly but reserved, reflecting her simple lifestyle and strong work ethic.', '* Recover more fully from her leg injury to visit her parents in Darkwater Crossing * Maintain her independence and continue working despite her physical limitations * Eventually save enough money to potentially open her own mining operation * Find a life partner who understands and respects her dedication to her work');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('synda_llanith', 'Synda Llanith is a resilient Dark Elf farmer who maintains Merryfair Farm alongside her husband Dravin, embodying the values of honest work and fair compensation despite the challenges of life in Skyrim. She serves as both a voice of reason for her bitter husband and a steadfast agricultural entrepreneur trying to forge a life in an often hostile land.', 'darkelf, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Synda and her husband Dravin relocated to Skyrim seeking better opportunities, only to face the harsh realities of Nordic prejudice and civil war. Their farm near Riften has been targeted by thieves and threatened by the ongoing civil conflict, leading to significant hardships that have tested their resolve and partnership.', 'Practical and level-headed, Synda maintains a diplomatic approach to dealing with both customers and authorities, often serving as the moderating influence on her more volatile husband. She demonstrates remarkable resilience and adaptability, balancing her Dunmer pride with the pragmatic needs of running a successful farm in foreign territory. Despite hardships, she maintains a strong work ethic and sense of fairness.', 'As a Dunmer, Synda has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of her race, with sharp, angular features typical of mer. Her years of farm work have given her a sturdy, weathered appearance, with strong hands and a straight-backed posture that speaks to her daily physical labor.', '* Dravin Llanith - Beloved husband and farming partner, whom she constantly tries to protect from his own rashness * Riften Guards - Maintains cautiously cordial relations to ensure protection for their farm * Local Farmers - Professional acquaintances with whom she maintains necessary business relations * Marise Aravel - Fellow Dunmer in Riften with whom she occasionally trades', 'Synda is a farmer and co-owner of Merryfair Farm, handling both agricultural duties and business transactions with customers. She manages crop cultivation, harvest coordination, and maintains fair trading practices with those who assist in gathering their produce.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Capable of basic self-defense with a dagger * Skilled in agricultural commerce and fair business practices * Proficient in basic food preservation and storage techniques', 'She speaks in a practical, direct manner with a slight Morrowind accent, often tempering her husband''s harsh words with diplomatic alternatives. Her tone is matter-of-fact but polite, reflecting her merchant mindset and desire to maintain positive relationships with customers.', '* Maintain a successful farming operation despite the challenges of civil war and prejudice * Eventually return to Morrowind when circumstances allow * Keep her husband safe from his own confrontational tendencies with authorities * Build enough savings to ensure a secure future for herself and Dravin');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('syndus', 'Syndus is a skilled Bosmer fletcher and merchant who has found a profitable niche serving the Thieves Guild from his shop in the Ragged Flagon. Known for his exceptional archery equipment and proud demeanor, he maintains a careful balance between legitimate business and catering to Riften''s criminal underbelly.', 'woodelf, archer, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, Syndus learned the art of fletching and bowcraft from master craftsmen in his homeland. He later migrated to Skyrim seeking new opportunities, eventually forming a mutually beneficial relationship with the Thieves Guild that provided him both protection and a steady stream of discerning customers.', 'Syndus exhibits the typical Bosmer traits of pride and self-assurance, often boasting about his craftsmanship and personal qualities. He maintains strong loyalty to the Thieves Guild, refusing to do business with anyone who has crossed them, while displaying a shrewd business sense that has helped him thrive in Riften''s underground economy.', 'As a Bosmer, Syndus has the characteristic slight build and nimble frame of his race, standing shorter than most other races in Skyrim. His features are sharp and angular, typical of mer heritage, with the distinctive pointed ears of his kind.', '* Thieves Guild - Trusted merchant affiliate and supplier * Delvin Mallory - Primary contact within the Guild who helped establish his business * Tonilia - Fellow merchant at the Ragged Flagon, professional relationship * Vekel the Man - Business associate at the Ragged Flagon', 'Syndus operates as a specialized merchant focusing on archery equipment and fletching services. His position as the Thieves Guild''s preferred bowyer gives him exclusive access to both legitimate customers and guild members seeking quality archery equipment.', '* Master fletcher capable of crafting superior bows and arrows * Expert knowledge of archery equipment and maintenance * Skilled negotiator and merchant * Traditional Bosmer archery techniques and bowcraft', 'Speaks with a confident, sometimes boastful tone typical of Bosmer merchants, often peppering his speech with references to his skill and craftsmanship. His accent carries traces of his Valenwood heritage, though tempered by years of living in Skyrim.', '* Maintain and expand his profitable position as the Thieves Guild''s premier archery supplier * Perfect his craft and reputation as Skyrim''s finest fletcher * Accumulate enough wealth to potentially expand his business operations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('synod_researcher', 'A dedicated Imperial scholar and member of the Synod organization who met her tragic end while investigating the mysterious Dwemer ruins of Mzulft. Her academic pursuit of ancient knowledge and magical artifacts represented the Synod''s ambitious efforts to consolidate magical power and understanding throughout Tamriel.', 'imperial, scholar, eastmarch, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in the Imperial City, she showed early aptitude for magic and scholarly pursuits, leading to her recruitment by the Synod. After years of research in the Imperial City''s Arcane University, she was selected for the prestigious but dangerous Mzulft expedition to study Dwemer focusing crystals and their relationship to magical energies across Tamriel.', 'Meticulous and detail-oriented, with an insatiable curiosity about Dwemer technology and magical theory. Though somewhat politically naive about the Synod''s true motives, she maintained unwavering dedication to academic pursuit and documentation, often working long hours in dangerous conditions to further her research.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with sharp features and calculating eyes, bearing the subtle magical marks of prolonged exposure to arcane energies. Her hands show calluses from countless hours of writing and handling magical implements, while her face carries the weathered look of someone who has spent considerable time in harsh climates.', '* The Synod Council - Direct superiors who commissioned her research expedition * Fellow Researchers - Close academic colleagues who shared her fate in Mzulft * College of Winterhold - Professional rivals, viewed with skepticism as per Synod policy * Local Nordic populations - Maintained cautious distance, viewing them as primitive and superstitious', 'Senior Researcher for the Synod organization, specializing in Dwemer artifice and magical energy networks. Her position involved both theoretical research and practical field work, requiring her to document and analyze ancient Dwemer technology while managing junior researchers.', '* Expert-level knowledge of Dwemer machinery and architectural principles * Advanced understanding of magical theory and energy manipulation * Proficient in Destruction and Alteration schools of magic * Skilled in academic writing and research documentation * Basic combat training with daggers for self-defense', 'Speaks in precise, academic language, frequently using technical terms and theoretical concepts to explain her work. Her Imperial accent carries the refined tones of extensive education, though she occasionally slips into excited rambling when discussing her research.', '* Uncover the secrets of Dwemer focusing crystals and their applications * Advance the Synod''s understanding of magical energy networks across Tamriel * Prove the superiority of Imperial magical research over rival organizations * Document and preserve ancient Dwemer knowledge for future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('taarie', 'Taarie is a skilled High Elf tailor and businesswoman who co-owns the upscale Radiant Raiment clothing shop in Solitude with her twin sister. Though critical of fashion choices, she represents the more diplomatic face of the business, combining Altmer sophistication with merchant practicality.', 'highelf, merchant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femaleelfhaughty', '', 'Born into the culturally sophisticated Altmer society, Taarie and her twin sister Endarie established themselves in Solitude to serve the fashion needs of Skyrim''s elite. Their choice of Solitude was strategic, as the city''s status as the seat of the High King made it the perfect location for a high-end clothing business catering to nobility and wealthy citizens.', 'While maintaining typical Altmer pride and high standards, Taarie is notably more diplomatic and socially adept than her sister, though she still freely offers unsolicited fashion advice. She takes genuine pride in her craft and believes in maintaining high cultural standards through proper dress, viewing herself as something of a fashion missionary to the less refined peoples of Skyrim.', 'As a High Elf, Taarie possesses the characteristic tall, slender build and golden skin tone of her race. Her features are angular and elegant, typical of Altmer physiognomy, and she carries herself with the natural grace common to her people.', '* Endarie - Twin sister and business partner, sharing a close but sometimes tense working relationship * Elisif the Fair - Important client and target for business expansion * Solitude''s Noble Class - Primary customer base and social connections * Vittoria Vici - Regular customer and business associate * Erikur - Prominent client and local thane', 'Taarie is a master tailor and co-owner of Radiant Raiment, Solitude''s premier clothing shop. Beyond basic merchantry, she serves as a fashion consultant to Solitude''s elite and manages the diplomatic aspects of the business while her sister handles day-to-day sales.', '* Expert tailoring and clothing design * Advanced knowledge of fabrics and materials * Skilled businesswoman and merchant * Diplomatic and social networking abilities * Basic alchemy knowledge for fabric dyes and treatments', 'Taarie speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary typical of educated Altmer, though she modulates her natural condescension to maintain customer relationships. Her speech patterns reflect her merchant background, combining courtly politeness with subtle marketing techniques.', '* Expand Radiant Raiment''s influence to become the premier clothing supplier for all of Skyrim''s nobility * Secure a permanent contract with the Blue Palace and Jarl Elisif * Elevate the fashion standards of Skyrim''s population * Establish a second shop location in another major city');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tacitus_sallustius', 'Tacitus Sallustius is a timid and inexperienced Imperial blacksmith apprentice working at Markarth''s public smithy under the stern tutelage of Ghorza gra-Bagol. Despite his clumsiness and lack of confidence, he maintains a persistent dedication to learning the craft, though his current abilities limit him primarily to making nails and basic metal fittings.', 'imperial, blacksmith, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born to a middle-class Imperial family, Tacitus likely came to Markarth seeking opportunity in the city''s renowned metalworking industry. His choice of apprenticeship under an Orc master smith suggests either limited options or a genuine desire to learn from the best, regardless of cultural differences. The transition from a presumably sheltered Imperial upbringing to the harsh realities of forge work in the unforgiving environment of Markarth has contributed to his nervous disposition.', 'Tacitus exhibits clear signs of anxiety and self-doubt, particularly when handling smithing tasks beyond his comfort zone. His nervous temperament manifests in physical flinching while working with hot metal, and he often second-guesses his abilities. Despite these insecurities, he shows remarkable persistence in continuing his apprenticeship under Ghorza''s harsh criticism, suggesting an underlying determination that contrasts with his outward timidity.', 'As an Imperial working daily at the forge, Tacitus likely has the typical robust build of his race, though perhaps not as muscular as more experienced smiths. His hands probably show the developing calluses and minor burns common to apprentice metalworkers, and his face likely bears the soot stains characteristic of someone working regularly at a forge.', '* Ghorza gra-Bagol - His mentor and master smith, who frequently criticizes his work but continues to train him * Moth gro-Bagol - Associated through his master Ghorza, though interaction is limited * Understone Keep residents - Casual acquaintances as he resides there * Markarth smithing customers - Limited interaction due to his apprentice status', 'Tacitus serves as an apprentice blacksmith at Markarth''s public smithy, primarily tasked with creating nails and basic metal fittings. His position is entry-level, involving basic maintenance of the forge and assisting his master with various tasks throughout the day, while gradually learning more complex aspects of the trade.', '* Basic metalworking abilities, specifically in nail-making and simple fittings * Foundational knowledge of forge operation and maintenance * Limited experience in weapon sharpening * Basic understanding of metal heating and tempering * Developing physical endurance for forge work', 'Tacitus speaks with frequent hesitation and uncertainty, often using filler words like ''uh'' and ''well.'' His tone is apologetic and self-deprecating, particularly when discussing his smithing abilities.', '* Improve his blacksmithing skills to advance beyond making basic nails * Gain enough confidence to handle more complex smithing tasks * Earn the respect and approval of his mentor Ghorza * Eventually establish himself as a competent blacksmith in his own right');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('takes-in-light', 'Takes-In-Light was a promising Argonian sorceress and student at the College of Winterhold who met her tragic end during an ill-fated expedition to Labyrinthian. Her cautious and perceptive nature proved insufficient to prevent the disaster that claimed her life and those of her fellow students, leaving her spirit to eternally replay the tragic events within the ancient ruins.', 'argonian, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_femaleargonian', '', 'Takes-In-Light came to Skyrim from Black Marsh to study at the College of Winterhold, drawn by its reputation for magical scholarship. She showed particular aptitude for magical studies and earned a place among an elite group of students chosen for advanced research. Her academic career ended tragically during an unauthorized expedition to Labyrinthian led by fellow student Savos Aren.', 'Takes-In-Light was characterized by her cautious and analytical nature, often serving as the voice of reason within her peer group. She possessed a gentle, introspective disposition that made her well-liked among her fellow students, though her tendency to question dangerous situations was sometimes dismissed by more ambitious colleagues. Despite her reservations about risky ventures, she displayed loyalty to her friends that ultimately led to her demise.', 'As an Argonian, Takes-In-Light had iridescent scales with lighter coloring typical of those who dwell in warmer regions of Black Marsh. Her eyes possessed the characteristic Argonian almond shape with a subtle glow common among magic practitioners. Her frame was slender and graceful, typical of magic-focused scholars rather than warriors.', '* Savos Aren - Fellow student who later became Arch-Mage, led the fatal expedition * Atmah - Close friend and fellow student mage * Elvali Veren - Fellow expedition member and College peer * Hafnar Ice-Fist - Colleague in the ill-fated exploration team * Girduin - Fellow student who perished in Labyrinthian * College of Winterhold Faculty - Respected mentors and teachers', 'Takes-In-Light served as an apprentice mage at the College of Winterhold, focusing on scholarly research and the advancement of magical knowledge. She participated in advanced studies and experimental magic projects alongside her fellow students, showing particular promise in theoretical magic applications.', '* Accomplished sorceress with expertise in multiple schools of magic * Skilled researcher with deep knowledge of magical theory * Proficient in magical defense and protective spells * Advanced understanding of ancient Nordic ruins and their magical properties * Capable alchemist with knowledge of rare ingredients', 'Takes-In-Light speaks with a thoughtful, measured tone, often posing questions rather than making declarations. Her speech patterns reflect her cautious nature, frequently using qualifiers and expressing concerns in a gentle, diplomatic manner.', '* Complete her advanced magical studies at the College of Winterhold * Uncover and document ancient magical knowledge * Protect her fellow students from dangerous magical experiments * Return to Black Marsh to share her magical expertise * Advance understanding of protective magic applications');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('talen-jei', 'Talen-Jei is a skilled Argonian bartender at the Bee and Barb in Riften who brings sophistication to his craft through his signature drink creations. He represents a rare example of an honest, hardworking citizen in the corrupt city, maintaining strong moral principles while pursuing romance with his beloved Keerava.', 'argonian, innkeeper, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally from Gideon in Black Marsh, Talen-Jei developed his bartending expertise and created his signature drinks before relocating to Riften several years ago. Upon arriving in the city, he found employment at the Bee and Barb where he met Keerava, leading him to put down roots in spite of the city''s criminal elements.', 'Talen-Jei is polite and professional, maintaining a friendly demeanor with customers while holding strong moral convictions. He shows unwavering loyalty to Keerava and deep respect for Argonian traditions, particularly regarding marriage customs. Though generally non-confrontational, he demonstrates quiet courage in standing against the Thieves Guild''s influence.', 'As an Argonian, Talen-Jei has scaled skin in muted earth tones with hints of green, typical of his race. His horns are well-maintained and his posture is proper and dignified, reflecting his professional nature. His movements are precise and measured, characteristic of someone who handles delicate glassware daily.', '* Keerava - Romantic interest and employer, whom he hopes to marry * Maven Black-Briar - Tense relationship due to her Thieves Guild connections * Thieves Guild - Strong animosity toward the organization and its members * Other Bee and Barb patrons - Maintains professional, cordial relationships * Riften citizens - Generally respected among the law-abiding population', 'Talen-Jei serves as the primary bartender at the Bee and Barb, where he is known for his three signature drinks: Velvet LeChance, White-Gold Tower, and Cliff Racer. Beyond mixing drinks, he helps maintain order in the establishment and assists Keerava with various inn-keeping duties.', '* Expert mixologist capable of creating unique alcoholic beverages * Proficient in customer service and hospitality management * Competent with a dagger for self-defense * Knowledge of Black Marsh traditions and customs * Basic business acumen and accounting abilities', 'Talen-Jei speaks in a polite, formal manner with careful enunciation and occasional use of honorifics like ''milord'' or ''milady.'' His tone is measured and professional, though it can become stern when discussing the Thieves Guild.', '* Marry Keerava according to traditional Argonian customs * Maintain the Bee and Barb as a respectable establishment in Riften * Resist and minimize the Thieves Guild''s influence on honest businesses * Create a stable and prosperous life with Keerava * Preserve and share Argonian cultural traditions in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('talsgar_the_wanderer', 'Talsgar the Wanderer is a charismatic Nord bard who has dedicated his life to exploring Skyrim''s wilderness while collecting and performing stories and songs of its people. More than just a simple musician, he is a capable warrior-poet who embodies the Nordic tradition of skalds, combining martial prowess with artistic expression.', 'nord, bard, traveler, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born to a merchant family in one of Skyrim''s holds, Talsgar rejected the settled life of commerce to pursue his calling as a wandering bard. He received formal training at the Bards College in Solitude, but found the structured academic environment too constraining for his free spirit. After graduating, he chose to take his talents on the road, learning the ways of survival and self-defense while gathering tales and melodies from every corner of Skyrim.', 'Talsgar is an eternally optimistic and curious soul who finds wonder in both grand adventures and simple moments of natural beauty. He maintains a cheerful disposition even in dangerous situations, viewing life''s challenges as opportunities for new stories. Though generally peaceful, he carries a warrior''s pride and won''t hesitate to defend himself or others when necessary.', 'A hardy Nord of average height with weather-worn features that speak to his years on the road. His muscular but lean build reflects the physical demands of his traveling lifestyle. His face bears the characteristic sharp features of a Nord, with bright eyes that sparkle when sharing tales.', '* Bards College - Maintains loose ties with his alma mater and occasionally contributes new songs * Various Innkeepers - Network of professional contacts who provide him lodging and performance venues * Fellow Travelers - Temporary friendships formed on the road * Bandits - Occasional adversaries who see him as an easy target but often underestimate his combat skills', 'Talsgar serves as a wandering bard, performing at inns and gatherings while collecting stories and songs from across Skyrim. He supplements his income through mining, hunting, and occasional mercenary work, though he considers himself primarily an artist and explorer.', '* Accomplished singer and instrumentalist trained at the Bards College * Capable swordsman with experience in self-defense * Skilled survivalist able to live off the land * Basic knowledge of destruction and restoration magic * Proficient in mining and resource gathering', 'Talsgar speaks with the refined vocabulary of a trained bard while maintaining the hearty, direct manner of a Nord. His voice carries both warmth and authority, perfectly suited for both storytelling and song.', '* Document and preserve the stories and songs of Skyrim''s people through first-hand experience * Discover new tales worthy of being immortalized in song * Experience every corner of Skyrim and perhaps beyond * Create a lasting legacy through his collected works and performances');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('talvas_fathryon', 'Talvas Fathryon is an ambitious but accident-prone Dark Elf conjurer serving as Master Neloth''s apprentice at Tel Mithryn. Despite his frequent magical mishaps and struggles with confidence, he perseveres in his studies of the arcane arts, driven by a genuine desire to master conjuration magic and earn his mentor''s respect.', 'darkelf, mage, solstheim, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Talvas showed early promise in conjuration magic which eventually caught the attention of Master Neloth. Though the details of how he became Neloth''s apprentice are unclear, he likely underwent significant trials to prove his worth, as House Telvanni is known for only accepting the most promising pupils. His journey to Solstheim and subsequent apprenticeship represents his first significant step toward becoming a true Telvanni wizard.', 'Talvas is eager to learn and deeply dedicated to his studies, but suffers from anxiety and self-doubt, particularly due to Neloth''s harsh teaching style and his own tendency to make mistakes. Despite frequent setbacks and his master''s cutting remarks, he maintains an optimistic attitude and shows remarkable resilience. His demeanor alternates between scholarly confidence when discussing theory and nervous uncertainty when attempting practical applications.', 'Talvas has the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his Dunmer race, with sharp, angular features typical of mer-folk. His frame is lean and scholarly rather than muscular, with the slightly hunched posture common to those who spend long hours poring over spell tomes.', '* Master Neloth - His demanding mentor and teacher, whom he both fears and respects * Varona Nelas - Fellow Tel Mithryn resident who worries about his dangerous experiments * Elynea Mothren - The tower''s mycologist who occasionally helps clean up after his failed experiments * Other Tel Mithryn residents - Generally cordial but distant relationships', 'As Master Neloth''s apprentice, Talvas assists with magical research, maintains the tower''s magical apparatus, and continues his own studies in conjuration magic. He serves as the secondary magical authority in Tel Mithryn when Neloth is occupied with more important matters.', '* Advanced knowledge of Conjuration magic, particularly in summoning Atronachs and Ash Guardians * Proficient in Destruction magic, capable of casting various elemental spells * Competent in defensive magic, including wards and flesh spells * Academic knowledge of Telvanni magical theory and practices * Basic alchemy and enchanting abilities', 'Talvas speaks with the formal diction typical of educated Dunmer, though his voice often carries undertones of nervousness and uncertainty. His speech patterns alternate between academic confidence when discussing magical theory and stammering hesitation when addressing practical matters or speaking to authority figures.', '* Master the art of conjuration magic and become a respected Telvanni wizard * Earn genuine praise and recognition from Master Neloth * Overcome his tendency toward magical accidents and prove himself worthy of his position * Eventually establish his own tower and take on apprentices of his own');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('talvur', 'Talvur was a Dark Elf miner whose tragic love story exemplifies both the hope and harsh realities of life in Skyrim. Despite his humble station as a laborer in Markarth''s silver mines, he dared to pursue a forbidden romance with a nobleman''s daughter that ultimately led to both their deaths in the unforgiving wilderness.', 'darkelf, peasant, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a working-class Dunmer family, Talvur migrated to Markarth seeking employment in the city''s lucrative silver mining industry. Through circumstances unknown, he met and fell in love with Karan, the daughter of a wealthy Nord nobleman who likely disapproved of their relationship due to both racial and class differences. Their forbidden romance eventually led them to attempt an ill-fated elopement across Skyrim''s dangerous wilderness.', 'Talvur demonstrated remarkable courage and determination, willing to risk everything for love despite the social and physical dangers involved. His decision to help Karan escape her family suggests a romantic and idealistic nature, while his careful planning of their escape route and supply cache indicates practical intelligence. He likely possessed the characteristic Dunmer pride and resilience, refusing to accept the social barriers that stood between him and his beloved.', 'As a Dunmer, Talvur had the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race. His work as a miner likely gave him a muscular, sturdy build, with calloused hands and the physical resilience required for such demanding labor.', '* Karan - Noble-born Nord lover who died alongside him during their attempted elopement * Karan''s Father - Unnamed nobleman who presumably opposed their relationship * Fellow Miners - Professional relationships from his work in Markarth''s silver mines * Markarth''s Dunmer Community - Likely maintained connections with other Dark Elves in the city', 'Talvur worked as a manual laborer in Markarth''s silver mines, a demanding but relatively well-paying profession in the city. His position would have placed him firmly in the working class, with long hours spent excavating precious ore from the ancient Dwemer tunnels beneath the city.', '* Experienced miner with knowledge of excavation techniques and mineral identification * Physical strength and endurance developed through years of mining work * Basic survival skills necessary for planning an escape through Skyrim''s wilderness * Likely familiar with basic weapon use for self-defense, as most travelers in Skyrim are', 'Given his working-class background and Dunmer heritage, Talvur likely spoke with the distinctive accent of his people, though perhaps softened by his time among the Nords. His speech would have been direct and practical, reflecting his occupation, though possibly more eloquent when expressing his feelings for Karan.', '* Escape with Karan to build a new life together away from social prejudices * Find acceptance for their relationship despite racial and class differences * Establish a stable future where they could live openly as a couple * Possibly return to Morrowind where their relationship might face less prejudice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tandil', 'Tandil is an accomplished High Elf sorcerer and member of the secretive Psijic Order, tasked with containing dangerous magical artifacts that threaten Mundus. His presence at the College of Winterhold during the Eye of Magnus crisis demonstrates his role as one of the Order''s agents responsible for maintaining magical balance across Tamriel.', 'highelf, mage, winterhold, psijic', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born on the isle of Artaeum, Tandil spent centuries studying the Old Ways under the Psijic Order''s strict guidance. His exceptional magical aptitude and unwavering dedication to maintaining cosmic balance earned him a position as one of the Order''s field agents, dispatched to handle magical anomalies and artifacts that threaten the stability of Mundus.', 'Tandil exhibits the characteristic aloofness and air of superiority common among both High Elves and Psijic Order members. He maintains a professional detachment when dealing with outsiders, speaking only when necessary and focusing solely on his assigned duties. His centuries of magical study have instilled in him a deep respect for the power of magic and the importance of containing dangerous artifacts.', 'Tandil possesses the tall, slender build typical of Altmer, with sharp angular features and the characteristic golden skin of his race. His face shows minimal signs of aging despite his considerable years, as is common among High Elves, though his eyes reflect the wisdom and experience of centuries.', '* Quaranir - Fellow Psijic Order member and mission leader during the Eye of Magnus crisis * Gelebros - Colleague in the Psijic Order who assists in containing the Eye * Ancano - Viewed as a dangerous threat due to his abuse of the Eye of Magnus * College of Winterhold - Maintains professional distance while recognizing their role as custodians of magical knowledge', 'Tandil serves as a senior member of the Psijic Order, specializing in the containment and management of dangerous magical artifacts. His position requires him to travel across Tamriel when powerful magical anomalies threaten the balance of Mundus, often working in concert with other Order members to address such threats.', '* Master-level expertise in Alteration and Mysticism magic * Advanced knowledge of temporal manipulation and teleportation magic * Extensive experience in magical artifact containment and assessment * Profound understanding of the Old Ways and ancient magical practices * Skilled in diplomatic interactions with other magical institutions', 'Tandil speaks with the refined, formal dialect typical of both High Elves and the Psijic Order, using precise and carefully chosen words. His tone carries an air of ancient wisdom and authority, though he speaks rarely and only when necessary.', '* Maintain the balance of magical forces across Mundus through careful monitoring and intervention * Preserve the secrecy and traditions of the Psijic Order * Prevent dangerous magical artifacts from falling into the wrong hands * Continue his personal studies of the Old Ways and ancient magic');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('taron_dreth', 'Taron Dreth is a self-proclaimed expert in Dwemer metallurgy and the controversial author of The Aetherium Wars who built his academic reputation by stealing research from his former colleague Katria. A ruthless opportunist masquerading as a scholar, he travels with mercenary protection while seeking to eliminate anyone who might expose his fraudulent claims to expertise.', 'darkelf, mage, reach, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally a scholar at an unknown institution, Dreth discovered Katria''s groundbreaking research into Aetherium and saw an opportunity to advance his own career. After stealing her work and publishing it under his own name, he deliberately discredited her attempts to expose him, leading to her eventual death while exploring Arkngthamz. Since then, he has carefully maintained his fraudulent reputation while eliminating any threats to his academic standing.', 'Arrogant and condescending, Dreth masks his intellectual insecurity with excessive bravado and claims of expertise. His paranoia about being exposed as a fraud manifests as aggressive behavior toward anyone who questions his authority on Dwemer metallurgy, and he''s willing to resort to violence to protect his reputation.', 'A middle-aged Dunmer with sharp, angular features typical of his race and a perpetual look of smug superiority. His frame is slight and scholarly rather than muscular, with the pale grayish skin characteristic of Dark Elves and the red eyes common to his people.', '* Katria - Former colleague whose research he stole and whose reputation he destroyed * Hired Mercenaries - Three paid bodyguards who protect him during his travels * Academic Community - Maintains superficial relationships while avoiding close scrutiny of his work * Markarth Silver-Bloods - Business association through his frequent stays at their inn', 'Taron Dreth maintains a public persona as a renowned scholar and author specializing in Dwemer metallurgy and ancient forging techniques. He supplements his academic income by selling his expertise as a consultant on Dwemer artifacts and metallurgical processes.', '* Basic understanding of Dwemer metallurgy, mostly plagiarized from Katria''s research * Competent destruction magic user specializing in elemental spells * Skilled in academic fraud and maintaining false credentials * Persuasive speaker capable of convincing others of his expertise', 'Speaks with an affected air of intellectual superiority, using academic terminology to intimidate and impress others. His speech is characterized by condescending tones and dismissive remarks toward those he considers beneath his scholarly status.', '* Maintain his fraudulent reputation as the world''s foremost expert in Dwemer metallurgy * Eliminate anyone who threatens to expose his plagiarism of Katria''s work * Acquire genuine Aetherium artifacts to validate his stolen research * Prevent the discovery of Katria''s original research notes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('taunting_adventurer', 'A confrontational warrior who roams Skyrim''s wilderness and frequents its inns, known for their aggressive and demeaning behavior towards travelers. This wandering fighter embodies the harsh warrior culture of Skyrim, testing the mettle of those they encounter through intimidation and sometimes violence.', 'nord, warrior, skyrimall', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into a culture that values strength and combat prowess, they spent years honing their fighting skills and developing a reputation as a formidable warrior. After becoming disillusioned with structured military life, they chose to become a wandering adventurer, testing their might against worthy opponents and building notoriety through confrontational encounters.', 'Arrogant and confrontational, they derive satisfaction from intimidating those they perceive as weak. Their aggressive behavior masks a deep-seated need to constantly prove their worth through dominance and combat prowess. Despite their hostile demeanor, they adhere to a personal code of honor that allows opponents to back down from confrontations.', 'Physically imposing with well-defined musculature developed through years of combat and training. Battle scars mark their body, worn as badges of honor that tell tales of past conflicts. Their stance is naturally aggressive, with squared shoulders and a domineering presence that commands attention.', '* Local Guards - Tense relationship due to frequent complaints about intimidation * Inn Keepers - Tolerated customer known for causing trouble * Fellow Mercenaries - Respected but not particularly liked due to their attitude * Common Folk - Generally feared and avoided due to their aggressive reputation', 'Independent adventurer who makes their living through a combination of mercenary work, bounty hunting, and occasional banditry. They frequent inns and travel Skyrim''s roads, seeking opportunities for profit and combat while building a reputation through intimidation.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat with specialized training in one-handed weapons * Proficient in intimidation tactics and verbal manipulation * Skilled in survival and wilderness navigation * Advanced knowledge of armor maintenance and weapon care', 'Uses confrontational and dismissive language, frequently employing Nordic insults like ''milk drinker'' and speaking with a commanding, aggressive tone. Their speech is direct and often condescending, designed to provoke reactions from others.', '* Prove their superiority through combat and intimidation * Build a fearsome reputation throughout Skyrim * Accumulate wealth and power through their martial prowess * Find worthy opponents who can provide a real challenge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('teeba-ei', 'Teeba-Ei is an Argonian scout turned miner who found unlikely refuge in Skyrim''s harsh climate after surviving a shipwreck. His unwavering loyalty to Sorli the Builder, who saved his life, leads him from humble mine worker to appointed housecarl when she becomes Jarl of Hjaalmarch under Stormcloak rule.', 'argonian, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally a scout from Black Marsh, Teeba-Ei was the sole survivor of a wrecked trader vessel that left him stranded in Skyrim''s frozen waters. Nearly dead from exposure, he wandered into Stonehills where Sorli the Builder took him in without pressing for details about his past. The mysterious circumstances of his shipwreck and his previous life in Black Marsh remain untold, though his scouting skills suggest possible military or exploratory experience.', 'Teeba-Ei is characterized by his steadfast loyalty and strong work ethic, despite his clear discomfort with Skyrim''s climate. He maintains a humble and formal demeanor, showing gratitude for his second chance at life while harboring a subtle melancholy about his circumstances. His third-person speech pattern suggests traditional Argonian cultural values and perhaps a formal upbringing.', 'As an Argonian, Teeba-Ei has the characteristic scaled skin and reptilian features of his race, with a long tail and horned head. His body shows the muscular development typical of someone engaged in daily physical labor, though perhaps leaner than most miners due to his scouting background.', '* Sorli the Builder - Devoted employer who saved his life, later becomes his Jarl * Jesper - Close friend and fellow miner at Rockwallow Mine * Gestur Rockbreaker - Mine boss who maintains a cordial working relationship with him * Other Stonehills miners - Coworkers with whom he shares camp life', 'Teeba-Ei works as a miner at Rockwallow Mine, spending long hours extracting iron ore. If Hjaalmarch falls to the Stormcloaks, he transitions to the role of housecarl for Jarl Sorli the Builder, splitting his time between guard duties in Morthal and mining in Stonehills.', '* Experienced scout with likely tracking and survival abilities * Proficient miner capable of long hours of physical labor * Basic combat training as evidenced by his housecarl duties * Survival expert, having endured shipwreck and extreme cold * Possible swimming and underwater breathing abilities typical of Argonians', 'Teeba-Ei speaks in a formal, third-person manner, always referring to himself by name rather than using personal pronouns. His speech patterns reflect both his Argonian heritage and a possible formal education or training.', '* Repay his life debt to Sorli through loyal service and hard work * Adapt to life in Skyrim despite its harsh climate * Fulfill his duties as housecarl if promoted to the position * Perhaps secretly yearns to return to his original scouting profession');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tekla', 'Tekla is a humble Nord woman who serves as maid to Dengeir of Stuhn in Falkreath, later rising to the prestigious position of steward if the Stormcloaks take control. Despite facing suspicion of espionage from her employer, she maintains her dignity and dedication to service, eventually earning enough trust to help govern an entire hold.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalecoward', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath, Tekla grew up alongside her sister Narri, both seeking honest work to make their way in life. She secured a position as Dengeir''s maid during his time as Jarl, continuing to serve him even after he was replaced by his nephew Siddgeir, demonstrating unwavering loyalty despite facing constant suspicion and accusations of spying.', 'Tekla is characterized by her humble and nervous disposition, often downplaying her own importance and expressing self-doubt about her capabilities. Despite her insecurities, she shows remarkable resilience and dedication to her duties, maintaining her composure even when faced with Dengeir''s paranoid accusations. She demonstrates strong ethical principles through her loyal service despite mistreatment.', 'A Nord woman of average height with the characteristic hardy build of her race. She maintains a neat, practical appearance befitting her service role, with features weathered by years of domestic labor. Her posture often reflects her nervous disposition, frequently appearing slightly hunched as if trying to make herself less noticeable.', '* Dengeir of Stuhn - Her employer who both suspects and trusts her, eventually promoting her to steward * Narri - Her sister who works at Dead Man''s Drink * Solaf - Her romantic partner and local merchant * Thadgeir - Dengeir''s brother who offers her encouragement and support * Jarl Siddgeir - Dengeir''s nephew whom she is suspected of spying for', 'Initially serves as a maid in Dengeir''s household, responsible for cleaning and maintaining his residence. If the Stormcloaks take control of Falkreath, she is promoted to steward, where she manages the hold''s affairs, sells land to prospective homeowners, and issues bounty contracts.', '* Experienced in household management and domestic duties * Diplomatic abilities in managing difficult personalities * Administrative capabilities in hold management * Basic literacy and accounting skills necessary for stewardship', 'Tekla speaks in a hesitant, self-effacing manner, often qualifying her statements with uncertainty. Her word choice reflects her humble station, using respectful terms of address and avoiding assertive language.', '* Prove herself worthy of the trust placed in her as steward * Support the people of Falkreath through competent administration * Maintain her relationship with Solaf despite political tensions * Navigate the complex political situation while staying loyal to Dengeir');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('teldryn_sero', 'Teldryn Sero is a highly skilled Dunmer spellsword and mercenary from Blacklight who combines martial prowess with destructive magic. A veteran warrior with centuries of combat experience, he has built a reputation as one of Morrowind''s finest blades-for-hire while maintaining an air of mystery behind his signature chitin helmet.', 'darkelf, warrior, mage, solstheim, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Born and raised in Blacklight, Morrowind, Teldryn has lived through multiple eras and claims to have met Saint Jiub, placing him at over 200 years old. After leaving his homeland, he spent time in Windhelm''s Gray Quarter before eventually settling in Raven Rock, where he built his reputation as an elite mercenary. His custom chitin armor, crafted by master smith Grendis Rolovo, stands as a testament to his professional success and dedication to his craft.', 'Teldryn is confident and self-assured, often boasting about his abilities and past exploits, though his actions prove his claims aren''t mere bravado. He shows a pragmatic approach to survival, demonstrated by his willingness to abandon a doomed employer rather than face certain death. Despite his mercenary nature, he maintains a code of honor and professional pride in his work.', 'A tall, athletic Dunmer with the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of his race. His facial features show the weathering of centuries, with sharp angles typical of Dunmeri physiognomy. His body bears the subtle scars and maintained muscle of a lifetime warrior.', '* Previous Patron - Unnamed Nord warrior who likely perished in a bandit camp * Grendis Rolovo - Master armorer who crafted his signature chitin armor * Geldis Sadri - Owner of the Retching Netch where Teldryn finds work * Various Raven Rock residents - Professional acquaintances who know him as a reliable mercenary', 'Teldryn works as a professional mercenary and spellsword, offering his services to paying clients at the Retching Netch cornerclub in Raven Rock. His reputation and high fee of 500 gold pieces reflect his elite status among sellswords.', '* Master-level spellsword combining one-handed weapons with destruction magic * Expert in Conjuration magic, particularly skilled with Flame Atronach summoning * Proficient in Destruction magic specializing in fire-based spells * Accomplished in light armor combat, particularly with chitin armor * Tactical combat expertise developed over centuries of battlefield experience', 'Speaks with the refined accent of a Morrowind-born Dunmer, using sophisticated vocabulary that reflects his centuries of experience. His tone is confident and sometimes boastful, but always professional, often peppering his speech with references to past adventures.', '* Maintain his reputation as one of Morrowind''s finest blades-for-hire * Accumulate wealth through his mercenary work while avoiding unnecessary risks * Find challenging but survivable contracts that match his considerable skills * Eventually return to Blacklight with enough wealth to retire in comfort');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('telrav', 'Telrav is a cunning Imperial bandit who operates an elaborate ambush scheme near Nilheim, posing as a distressed merchant to lure compassionate travelers to their doom. His carefully crafted persona of a helpless victim masks a calculating killer who leads an organized group of bandits specializing in deception-based robbery and murder.', 'imperial, thief, archer, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Telrav likely developed his skills in deception and archery through years of criminal activity before establishing himself in Skyrim. He chose the strategic location near Nilheim for its isolation and proximity to well-traveled roads, setting up an elaborate trap using a destroyed cart as bait and coordinating with fellow bandits to create a sophisticated ambush operation.', 'Telrav is a masterful actor and manipulator who expertly plays on others'' sympathy and goodwill. His calculated approach to banditry reveals a patient, intelligent criminal who prefers elaborate schemes over direct confrontation, though he shows no moral hesitation in murdering those he deceives. Despite his leadership role, he displays strong self-preservation instincts, often fleeing or becoming passive when his plans go awry.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered appearance typical of someone who spends much time outdoors. His build is lean and athletic, suited to his role as an archer, with the practiced movements of an experienced fighter. His features are deliberately unremarkable, helping him maintain his convincing disguise as a common merchant.', '* Nilheim Bandits - Leader and coordinator of their ambush operations * Local Merchants - Targets and unwitting sources of intelligence about traveler patterns * Fellow Imperial Bandits - Likely maintains connections with other criminal groups * Victims - Views them merely as marks to be exploited, showing no remorse', 'Telrav serves as both the leader and primary lure for the Nilheim bandit operation. His specific role involves maintaining his merchant disguise, coordinating with his fellow bandits, and personally participating in the ambush and elimination of targets.', '* Expert archer with precise aim and knowledge of advanced bowmanship * Master of deception and performance, capable of maintaining convincing disguises * Tactical planning and group coordination * Survival skills and wilderness navigation * Leadership abilities in managing criminal operations', 'Telrav alternates between two distinct speech patterns: a polite, desperate tone when maintaining his victim facade, and a more confident, threatening manner when revealing his true nature. His vocabulary and delivery are carefully chosen to match his current persona, demonstrating significant verbal intelligence.', '* Maintain and expand the profitable Nilheim ambush operation * Acquire wealth through continued deception and robbery * Avoid detection by hold guards and bounty hunters * Potentially establish additional similar operations in other locations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('temba_wide-arm', 'Temba Wide-Arm is a hardworking and strong-willed Nord businesswoman who owns and operates Ivarstead''s sawmill. She represents the archetypal Nordic work ethic combined with entrepreneurial spirit, though her determination is constantly tested by the local bear population that threatens her livelihood.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Temba invested her entire life savings to purchase and operate the Ivarstead sawmill. The name ''Wide-Arm'' likely comes from her years of physical labor and reputation for being able to handle large lumber with ease. Her business acumen and determination led her to maintain one of the few successful enterprises in the small town of Ivarstead, despite increasing challenges from the local wildlife.', 'Temba is a straightforward, no-nonsense individual with a quick temper, particularly when it comes to bears and business setbacks. She shows strong determination and resilience in the face of adversity, though this often manifests as irritability and impatience, especially towards her apprentice Gwilin. Despite her gruff exterior, she has a strong sense of responsibility and commitment to her business and community.', 'A sturdy Nord woman with the muscular build typical of someone who engages in daily physical labor. Her arms are particularly well-developed from years of handling lumber, living up to her surname. She bears the weathered features of someone who works outdoors in all conditions.', '* Gwilin - Her apprentice at the mill, often the target of her frustration and criticism * Wilhelm - Owner of Vilemyr Inn where she lodges * Local hunters - Potential allies in her ongoing battle against bears * Bears - Considered enemies that threaten her livelihood', 'Temba is the owner and operator of Ivarstead''s sawmill, responsible for providing lumber to the local community and managing all aspects of the business. She personally oversees the daily operations, from selecting trees to processing lumber, while also managing her apprentice and dealing with various business challenges.', '* Expert knowledge of lumber and woodworking * Considerable physical strength and endurance from years of mill work * Business management and entrepreneurial skills * Basic combat abilities for self-defense against wildlife * Skilled in identifying quality lumber and assessing tree damage', 'She speaks in a direct, often frustrated tone, frequently punctuating her sentences with complaints about bears or business troubles. Her vocabulary is practical and straightforward, reflecting her no-nonsense approach to life.', '* Eliminate the bear threat to protect her lumber supply and business * Expand her mill''s operations once the bear situation is under control * Train her apprentice Gwilin to be more competent and reliable * Maintain a successful business despite the challenges of operating in a small town');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thadgeir', 'Thadgeir is a seasoned Nord warrior and brother to the former Jarl of Falkreath who maintains deep connections to the town''s martial heritage and burial traditions. He serves as a voice of reason between his paranoid brother Dengeir and the current political climate, while honoring the countless warriors laid to rest in Falkreath''s ancient graveyard.', 'nord, warrior, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born into the noble family of Falkreath, Thadgeir spent his youth as a warrior, fighting alongside companions like Berit in service to the hold. While his brother Dengeir rose to become Jarl, Thadgeir remained a steadfast protector of Falkreath''s traditions and people, witnessing the political transition when their nephew Siddgeir took the throne from Dengeir.', 'Thadgeir exhibits the stoic dignity typical of Nord warriors, combining martial pride with a deep respect for tradition and the fallen. Unlike his suspicious brother, he shows compassion and reason, particularly in his defense of Tekla and his regular honoring of deceased companions. He carries himself with the quiet confidence of a veteran warrior while maintaining diplomatic ties between the old and new political orders.', 'A weathered Nord warrior with the strong build and hardy constitution typical of his race. His features show the marks of age and battle experience, yet he maintains the physical capability to perform manual labor like wood chopping well into his later years.', '* Dengeir - Brother and former Jarl, whom he supports while tempering his paranoid tendencies * Siddgeir - Nephew and current Jarl, maintaining a diplomatic if distant relationship * Tekla - Household servant he defends against his brother''s suspicions * Berit - Deceased war companion whose memory he honors * Runil - Priest of Arkay with whom he interacts regarding burial rites', 'Though technically retired from active military service, Thadgeir serves as an informal elder of Falkreath, contributing through manual labor and maintaining social connections between the old guard and current leadership. He helps manage his brother''s household while performing daily tasks that benefit the community.', '* Experienced warrior trained in traditional Nord combat techniques * Knowledgeable about Falkreath''s history and burial traditions * Diplomatic mediator between various town factions * Practical laborer skilled in woodcutting and household management', 'Speaks in a direct, solemn manner typical of Nord warriors, often making references to Falkreath''s history and fallen heroes. His tone carries the weight of experience while remaining diplomatic and measured.', '* Maintain peace between his brother''s old guard and the new political establishment * Preserve and honor Falkreath''s traditions as a burial ground for great warriors * Support and protect the household staff from his brother''s increasing paranoia * Ensure proper respect and remembrance for fallen warriors');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thaena', 'Thaena is a formidable Nord woman who serves the dual role of housecarl and wife to Jarl Korir of Winterhold, embodying the harsh resilience of Nord culture in the face of adversity. She stands as one of the last defenders of Winterhold''s traditional values, maintaining a deep-seated resentment toward the College of Winterhold while striving to preserve what remains of the once-great city.', 'nord, noble, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Winterhold, Thaena witnessed firsthand the city''s decline following the Great Collapse, which shaped her bitter attitude toward magic and the College. Her martial prowess and unwavering loyalty to Nordic traditions earned her the position of housecarl to Jarl Korir, eventually leading to their marriage and the birth of their son Assur. Having lived through Winterhold''s transformation from a prosperous city to a mere shadow of its former self, she carries the weight of its history and the responsibility of maintaining what little dignity remains.', 'Thaena is a stern, pragmatic woman whose harsh exterior reflects the unforgiving environment of Winterhold. She harbors deep-seated resentment toward the College of Winterhold and maintains an unwavering belief that magic was responsible for her home''s destruction. Despite her hardened demeanor, she shows fierce devotion to her family and takes pride in raising her son Assur to be strong in the face of adversity.', 'Thaena possesses the sturdy build typical of Nord women, with weather-worn features that speak to years of enduring Winterhold''s harsh climate. Her face bears the stern lines of someone who has weathered many hardships, while her strong physique reflects her military training as a housecarl.', '* Jarl Korir - Husband and liege, whom she serves as both wife and housecarl * Assur - Son whom she is raising to be resilient in the face of hardship * Birna - Local merchant with whom she maintains a somewhat terse relationship * College of Winterhold - Institutional enemy she blames for Winterhold''s decline * Imperial Legion - Bitter enemies should they take control of Winterhold', 'Thaena serves as both housecarl and wife to Jarl Korir, making her one of the most important figures in what remains of Winterhold. Her duties include protecting the Jarl, managing the Jarl''s Longhouse, and maintaining the traditional Nordic customs of the hold.', '* Trained warrior capable of defending her Jarl as his housecarl * Experienced in household management and court protocol * Skilled in traditional Nordic weapons and combat techniques * Knowledgeable in local history and Nordic traditions * Practiced in survival skills necessary for Winterhold''s harsh climate', 'Thaena speaks in a direct, often bitter tone, using plain language that reflects her practical nature and Nordic heritage. Her speech is characterized by frank assessments and occasional sharp remarks, particularly when discussing the College or Winterhold''s decline.', '* Preserve what remains of Winterhold''s dignity and traditional Nordic values * Raise her son Assur to become a strong leader who can help restore Winterhold * See the College of Winterhold removed from the city * Maintain Nordic independence and resist Imperial control * Help restore Winterhold to its former glory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('agent_sanyon', 'Agent Sanyon was a dedicated Thalmor Justiciar whose zealous pursuit of illegal Talos worship led to his demise at the Shrine of Talos in Falkreath Hold. A loyal servant of the Aldmeri Dominion, he represented the Thalmor''s ruthless commitment to enforcing the White-Gold Concordat through investigation and suppression of outlawed religious practices.', 'highelf, thalmor', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Born and raised in the Summerset Isles during the rise of Thalmor influence, Sanyon was indoctrinated from an early age in Aldmeri supremacist ideology. He distinguished himself through unwavering dedication to Thalmor principles, eventually earning a position as a Justiciar assigned to Skyrim operations. His appointment to investigate Talos worship in the Lake Ilinalta region came directly from First Emissary Elenwen, indicating his trusted status within the organization.', 'Sanyon embodied the typical Thalmor traits of racial superiority and religious intolerance, viewing humans as inferior beings worthy only of subjugation. His dedication to duty bordered on fanaticism, willing to pursue suspected Talos worshippers even in remote and dangerous locations. Like many Justiciars, he likely displayed the characteristic Thalmor arrogance and contempt for local Nordic customs.', 'Tall and slender like most Altmer, with the characteristic golden skin and angular features of his race. His face likely bore the stern, perpetually disdainful expression common among Thalmor agents, with sharp cheekbones and narrow eyes that conveyed his sense of superiority.', '* Elenwen - Direct superior who trusted him with sensitive investigations * Fellow Thalmor Justiciars - Professional colleagues in enforcing the White-Gold Concordat * Talos Worshippers - Targets of investigation and persecution * Local Nords - Viewed with suspicion and contempt as potential heretics', 'As a Thalmor Justiciar, Sanyon''s primary duty was investigating and suppressing illegal Talos worship throughout Skyrim. He operated with significant autonomy, conducting surveillance, interrogations, and enforcement actions under the authority of the Aldmeri Dominion.', '* Proficient in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Trained in intelligence gathering and interrogation techniques * Skilled in Alteration magic for self-defense * Expert in identifying signs of illegal Talos worship * Competent swordsman with elven weapon training', 'Spoke with the characteristic haughty accent and formal diction of the Altmer upper class. His speech likely emphasized his perceived superiority, using condescending tones and sophisticated vocabulary to intimidate those he questioned.', '* Advance within the Thalmor hierarchy through successful persecution of Talos worship * Eliminate all traces of Talos worship in his assigned region * Prove himself worthy of higher responsibilities within the Thalmor organization * Maintain Aldmeri Dominion control over religious practices in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tharstan', 'Tharstan is a dedicated historian and scholar who has made the remote Skaal Village his temporary home while studying the unique culture and traditions of its people. Originally from Solitude, this elderly researcher combines academic rigor with an adventurous spirit, braving ancient Nordic ruins to uncover historical knowledge while maintaining respectful relationships with the traditionally private Skaal community.', 'nord, scholar, solstheim, skall', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Tharstan spent much of his early career researching Nordic history in the College of Winterhold''s archives and exploring ancient ruins across Skyrim. After publishing several well-received historical texts, he became fascinated with the mysterious Skaal culture and relocated to Solstheim to document their traditions and beliefs, becoming one of the few outsiders to gain their trust and acceptance.', 'Tharstan is scholarly and methodical, yet maintains an infectious enthusiasm for discovery that belies his advanced age. He approaches his research with deep respect for local customs and beliefs, earning him rare acceptance among the typically insular Skaal. Though primarily academic in nature, he possesses surprising courage when the pursuit of knowledge requires venturing into dangerous places.', 'An elderly Nord with a thin frame and weathered features that speak to a lifetime of academic pursuit. His face bears the wrinkles of age and countless hours spent studying in candlelight, while his posture remains remarkably straight despite his years. His hands show the delicate dexterity of someone accustomed to handling fragile manuscripts and artifacts.', '* Fanari Strong-Voice - Respects him as a thoughtful outsider and maintains a warm, professional relationship * Nikulas - Young villager who enjoys listening to Tharstan''s stories and travel tales * Skaal Villagers - Generally accepting of his presence despite their usual wariness of outsiders * Academic Community in Skyrim - Respected author and researcher among scholarly circles', 'Tharstan serves as both a historian and author, dedicating himself to documenting the history and traditions of Solstheim''s indigenous peoples. His current project involves writing the definitive history of the Skaal people, while also conducting first-hand research into ancient Nordic ruins and artifacts across the island.', '* Expert historian with extensive knowledge of Nordic history and culture * Accomplished author and researcher with multiple published works * Basic survival skills necessary for extended field research * Capable of deciphering ancient Nordic writings and inscriptions * Elementary self-defense abilities with an iron dagger', 'Speaks in an educated, scholarly manner with careful attention to detail and accuracy. His vocabulary is extensive but accessible, and he often peppers his speech with historical references while maintaining a warm, engaging tone.', '* Complete his definitive historical account of the Skaal people and their traditions * Document and preserve the ancient Nordic history of Solstheim * Gain deeper understanding of the connection between the Skaal and the All-Maker * Share his knowledge with future generations through his writings');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('the_caller', 'The Caller is a formidable High Elf mage and leader of a rogue magical research group operating from Fellglow Keep, known for her unauthorized acquisition of rare magical texts from the College of Winterhold. She represents a faction of independent mages who reject the College''s restrictive approach to magical research, preferring to pursue knowledge through more direct and potentially dangerous means.', 'highelf, mage, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, The Caller grew frustrated with what she perceived as overcautious and limiting research protocols. She established her own splinter group of like-minded mages, setting up operations in Fellglow Keep where she could conduct magical experiments without oversight or restriction. Her particular interest in ancient elven and mystical texts led her to orchestrate the theft of several rare volumes from the College''s library.', 'The Caller exhibits the characteristic arrogance and superiority complex common among High Elves, enhanced by her considerable magical prowess and leadership position. She maintains a coldly intellectual approach to her work, viewing both people and magical artifacts as tools for advancing her research, while displaying contempt for what she considers lesser minds. Despite her dismissive attitude, she demonstrates pragmatic reasoning when dealing with threats or negotiations.', 'Tall and slender with the characteristic golden skin and angular features of the Altmer race. Her face bears the subtle signs of aging that come with extended magical study, with sharp cheekbones and intense eyes that reflect her years of arcane practice.', '* Orthorn - Former subordinate who stole books from the College of Winterhold on her behalf * College of Winterhold - Antagonistic relationship due to theft of valuable texts * Fellglow Keep Mages - Loyal followers who respect her leadership and magical expertise * Local Populations - Hostile relationship due to aggressive magical experiments and necromantic practices', 'The Caller serves as the leader and primary researcher of the Fellglow Keep mages, directing their various magical experiments and studies. She maintains a particular focus on ancient magical knowledge and artifacts, especially those related to elven history and mystical practices.', '* Master-level destruction magic with emphasis on elemental spells * Expert knowledge of ancient magical texts and elven history * Advanced understanding of ritual magic and experimental magical theory * Skilled leader and coordinator of magical research projects * Proficient in defensive magic and magical barriers', 'She speaks with a refined, educated accent typical of well-trained mages, using sophisticated vocabulary and maintaining a condescending tone. Her manner of speech reflects both her Altmer heritage and academic background, often employing subtle mockery and intellectual superiority in her interactions.', '* Advance magical research beyond the restrictive boundaries set by the College of Winterhold * Uncover the secrets contained within ancient magical texts, particularly those related to elven history * Establish her group as a legitimate alternative to traditional magical institutions * Expand her influence and collection of rare magical knowledge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thomas', 'Thomas was an ambitious but ill-fated Breton bandit wizard who met his demise in Bleak Falls Barrow while attempting to hunt a frost troll. Despite his considerable magical abilities and confidence in his skills, his adventure ended tragically when he slipped and fell to his death, serving as a cautionary tale about the dangers that lurk within Nordic ruins.', 'breton, mage', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Originally trained in magic at an unknown institution, Thomas turned to banditry to supplement his income and fund his magical research. He developed a particular interest in Nordic ruins and their mysteries, studying various spells and collecting magical artifacts from these dangerous locations. His final expedition to Bleak Falls Barrow was motivated by reports of a frost troll that he believed he could defeat with his fire magic.', 'Thomas was overconfident in his magical abilities, often underestimating the dangers he faced in his pursuits. He displayed a scholarly interest in magic combined with a reckless adventuring spirit, suggesting a complex character who balanced intellectual pursuits with dangerous practical applications. His written note reveals both his self-assurance and his fatal miscalculation of the risks involved in his final expedition.', 'A middle-aged Breton of average height with the typical slight build common to magic users. His hands showed the calluses characteristic of frequent spellcasting, while his physique suggested someone who spent considerable time exploring ruins and engaging in physical activity.', '* Local Bandits - Loose associations with various bandit groups in the region * Fellow Treasure Hunters - Competitive relationships with other adventurers seeking valuable artifacts * Nordic Ruins Scholars - Professional contacts who shared information about potential exploration sites * Fence Contacts - Business relationships with those who helped sell his acquired goods', 'Thomas worked as a freelance treasure hunter and bandit wizard, combining his magical expertise with tomb raiding. He specialized in exploring Nordic ruins and acquiring valuable artifacts, using his magical abilities to overcome obstacles and defend against threats.', '* Proficient in Alteration magic, particularly the Oakflesh spell for personal protection * Skilled in multiple Destruction spell types including Flames, Frost, and Sparks * Competent in Restoration magic, capable of casting Healing and Lesser Ward * Advanced magical recovery abilities through knowledge of Magicka Recovery techniques * Basic proficiency with daggers for close-quarter combat', 'Thomas spoke with the educated tone of a trained mage, often using technical magical terminology and academic references. His writing style suggests he was well-versed in magical theory and documentation.', '* Master increasingly powerful destruction spells to enhance his combat capabilities * Accumulate wealth through the exploration of ancient Nordic ruins * Document and study the magical secrets hidden within Skyrim''s ancient tombs * Prove himself as a capable solo adventurer worthy of respect in the treasure hunting community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thonar_silver-blood', 'Thonar Silver-Blood is a ruthless Nord businessman who, alongside his brother Thongvor, controls much of Markarth''s economy and underground politics through the influential Silver-Blood family. He masterminds a complex web of corruption, manipulating both the city''s legitimate business interests and its criminal elements, including a secret arrangement with the Forsworn rebels.', 'nord, noble, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born into the wealthy Silver-Blood family, Thonar grew up learning the intricacies of Markarth''s political and economic landscape. Following the Markarth Incident, he orchestrated a secret deal with Madanach, the King in Rags, to maintain control over the Forsworn while expanding his family''s influence through both legitimate and illegitimate means. His marriage to Betrid was arranged purely for political advancement, though her eventual murder by the Forsworn would reveal unexpected emotional vulnerabilities.', 'Thonar is calculating, ruthless, and supremely confident in his family''s power over Markarth. He exhibits strong narcissistic traits, viewing others as tools to be used and discarded, while maintaining a veneer of aristocratic sophistication. Despite his cold exterior, he can be rattled when events spiral beyond his control, particularly regarding matters of family.', 'A well-built Nord male with the bearing of nobility, carrying himself with an air of superiority. His features are sharp and stern, weathered by years of conducting business in the harsh climate of the Reach. His physical appearance reflects his wealthy status, though he maintains the hardy constitution typical of Nord ancestry.', '* Thongvor Silver-Blood - Brother and business partner who handles political matters * Betrid Silver-Blood - Wife in a loveless political marriage, later murdered by Forsworn * Madanach - Secret business arrangement controlling the Forsworn * Rhiada - Treasury House clerk and possible object of inappropriate attention * Nepos the Nose - Forsworn conspirator and business associate * Donnel and Nana Ildene - House servants under his employ', 'Thonar serves as the operational leader of the Silver-Blood family''s business empire, managing their vast holdings including Cidhna Mine and numerous properties throughout Markarth. He operates as the family''s primary negotiator and enforcer, handling both legitimate business dealings and criminal enterprises while maintaining the family''s iron grip on the city''s economy.', '* Expert in business management and economic manipulation * Skilled negotiator and intimidator * Competent warrior with training in traditional Nord combat techniques * Master manipulator with extensive knowledge of political intrigue * Proficient at maintaining complex criminal networks', 'Thonar speaks with the refined accent of Markarth nobility, though his tone often carries underlying threats and condescension. His vocabulary is sophisticated but direct, frequently employing subtle implications and double meanings to convey both authority and menace.', '* Maintain and expand the Silver-Blood family''s control over Markarth''s economy and politics * Keep the Forsworn under control through his arrangement with Madanach * Eliminate any threats to his family''s power and influence * Secure his position as the true power behind Markarth''s throne');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thongvor_silver-blood', 'Thongvor Silver-Blood is a powerful and influential Nord nobleman from one of Markarth''s wealthiest families, known for his fierce support of the Stormcloak rebellion and deep-seated hatred of Imperial rule. As the head of the Silver-Blood family, he wields considerable economic and political influence in the Reach, eventually becoming Jarl if the Stormcloaks take control of Markarth.', 'nord, noble, warrior, reach, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into the wealthy and influential Silver-Blood family, Thongvor grew up in Markarth during a time of relative peace before the Great War. He witnessed firsthand the aftermath of the Markarth Incident, where Ulfric Stormcloak helped reclaim the city from the Forsworn, only to see the Empire later betray their promise to restore Talos worship. This event, combined with his family''s long-standing power in the Reach, shaped his strong anti-Imperial stance and support for the Stormcloak cause.', 'Thongvor is aggressive, confrontational, and deeply distrustful of Imperial authority and those he perceives as their supporters. He displays a strong sense of Nord pride and tradition, coupled with an uncompromising attitude toward those who oppose his views. His family''s wealth and influence have given him an air of entitlement and superiority, particularly evident in his harsh stance toward the Forsworn and non-Nord residents of the Reach.', 'A sturdy, well-built Nord male with the characteristic strong features of his race. His face bears the weathered look of a seasoned warrior, with stern eyes that reflect his harsh demeanor. His physical presence commands attention, befitting his status as a member of one of Markarth''s most prominent families.', '* Thonar Silver-Blood - Brother and business partner in the family''s various enterprises * Jarl Igmund - Political rival whom he views as an Imperial puppet * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respected ally and leader of the rebellion he supports * Brother Verulus - Antagonistic relationship due to suspicions of Imperial sympathy * The Forsworn - Considers them criminals and rebels deserving harsh punishment', 'Thongvor serves as a leading member of the Silver-Blood family, helping to manage their vast business interests including the Treasury House and Cidhna Mine. If the Stormcloaks take control of the Reach, he becomes Jarl of Markarth, ruling with a firm hand against any perceived threats to Nord sovereignty.', '* Experienced warrior trained in traditional Nord combat techniques * Skilled politician and negotiator in matters of business and governance * Natural leader with strong command presence * Adept at managing business operations and political relationships', 'Speaks in a direct, confrontational manner with a strong Nordic accent, often using aggressive tones and showing clear disdain for those he considers enemies of Skyrim. His speech reflects his privileged background while maintaining the rough edge characteristic of Nord warriors.', '* Secure Stormcloak control over Markarth and the Reach * Eliminate Forsworn influence through aggressive suppression and imprisonment * Restore traditional Nord values and Talos worship to the Reach * Expand Silver-Blood family influence and wealth throughout Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thonjolf', 'Thonjolf is a dedicated Nord housecarl who serves Kraldar with unwavering loyalty and efficiency in Winterhold. His position evolves from trusted household servant to official housecarl when Kraldar becomes Jarl under Imperial control, demonstrating his commitment to both his master and the potential prosperity of Winterhold.', 'nord, peasant, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in Winterhold during its decline, Thonjolf likely came from a family that served Kraldar''s once-powerful clan. His deep understanding of Winterhold''s politics and steadfast dedication to Kraldar suggests he has spent most of his adult life in service to the noble family, watching the city''s gradual deterioration while maintaining hope for its restoration.', 'Thonjolf is diligent, professional, and takes immense pride in his work, often expressing frustration with those who don''t share his strong work ethic. He maintains a respectful and formal demeanor, showing particular disdain for the lazy and unreliable, while remaining diplomatic in his duties. His loyalty to Kraldar extends beyond mere employment to genuine belief in his master''s vision for Winterhold.', 'As a Nord, Thonjolf likely possesses the typical robust build and hardy constitution of his race. His years of service and physical labor have likely given him a strong, capable physique, though perhaps showing signs of age through his mature features.', '* Kraldar - His master and liege, whom he serves with absolute loyalty and dedication * Malur Seloth - Strong dislike for his unreliability and poor work ethic * Arch-Mage Aren - Professional respect through his duties as messenger for Kraldar * College of Winterhold - Maintains diplomatic relations on behalf of Kraldar', 'Thonjolf serves as Kraldar''s housecarl, managing household affairs and acting as personal assistant and bodyguard. His duties expand significantly if Kraldar becomes Jarl, where he takes on more official responsibilities in the Jarl''s court while maintaining his role as protector and confidant.', '* Proficient in basic combat with focus on defensive techniques and dagger usage * Experienced in household management and servant coordination * Diplomatic skills developed through years of representing Kraldar''s interests * Knowledge of proper court etiquette and protocol', 'Thonjolf speaks in a formal, respectful manner befitting his position, often emphasizing his busy schedule and duties. His speech patterns reflect his Nord heritage while maintaining the professional tone expected of a housecarl.', '* Support Kraldar''s ambitions to become and remain Jarl of Winterhold * Help restore Winterhold to its former glory through loyal service * Maintain efficient management of Kraldar''s household and affairs * Foster better relations between Kraldar''s court and the College of Winterhold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thonnir', 'Thonnir is a hardworking Nord lumberjack and devoted family man whose life is upended by the mysterious disappearance of his wife Laelette in Morthal. Despite his simple background, he shows remarkable courage when confronting supernatural threats to his community, being the only townsperson willing to face vampires directly to learn the truth about his wife''s fate.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Morthal, Thonnir established himself as a reliable worker at Jorgen''s mill, eventually starting a family with his wife Laelette and having a son named Virkmund. His peaceful life was shattered when Laelette vanished, initially believing she had left to join the Stormcloaks, only to later discover she had been turned into a vampire by Alva''s influence.', 'Thonnir is a practical, straightforward man who values honest work and family above all else. While initially appearing cautious and somewhat fearful of Morthal''s growing dangers, he reveals tremendous courage when faced with supernatural threats, demonstrating that his love for family overcomes his fears. He struggles with telling his son the truth about Laelette''s fate, showing his protective nature as a father.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the muscular build typical of someone who performs physical labor daily. His hands are calloused from years of handling lumber, and his face shows the weathering of someone who works outdoors in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Laelette - His wife, turned vampire and ultimately killed * Virkmund - His young son who he struggles to protect from harsh truths * Jorgen - His employer at the lumber mill * Alva - Initially a townsperson he trusted, later revealed as the vampire who corrupted his wife * Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - Local authority he looks to for protection', 'Thonnir works as a lumberjack at Jorgen''s mill, processing lumber and performing various woodcutting duties. He maintains a regular schedule, working from early morning until evening, and sells lumber to travelers when Hearthfire construction is available.', '* Proficient in woodcutting and lumber processing * Capable with a war axe for both work and self-defense * Basic combat abilities, showing courage in dangerous situations * Knowledge of local forestry and wood types * Experience in physical labor and construction work', 'Thonnir speaks in a direct, unembellished manner typical of working-class Nords, often expressing his concerns and emotions plainly. His vocabulary is simple but earnest, reflecting his practical nature and straightforward worldview.', '* Protect and provide for his son Virkmund in the absence of his mother * Find a way to explain Laelette''s fate to Virkmund when he''s ready * Maintain a stable life in Morthal despite the town''s growing dangers * Continue his work as a lumberjack to support his family');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thorald_gray-mane', 'Thorald Gray-Mane is a proud Nord warrior and Stormcloak sympathizer from the respected Gray-Mane clan of Whiterun who endured brutal Thalmor interrogation at Northwatch Keep. His unwavering loyalty to his beliefs and remarkable resilience in the face of torture exemplify the steadfast Nordic spirit, making him a symbol of resistance against Imperial and Thalmor oppression.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born into the prestigious Gray-Mane family of Whiterun, Thorald grew up learning the values of honor, tradition, and Nordic culture from his parents Eorlund and Fralia. He chose to support the Stormcloak rebellion out of deep conviction in their cause, participating in battles against the Imperial Legion before his capture and subsequent transfer to Thalmor custody at Northwatch Keep, where he endured extensive interrogation without breaking.', 'Thorald exhibits exceptional mental fortitude and unwavering dedication to his beliefs, refusing to break under Thalmor torture. He demonstrates deep loyalty to his family and the Stormcloak cause, while maintaining a cautious and strategic mindset developed during his imprisonment. Despite his hardships, he retains a sense of honor and gratitude, showing genuine appreciation to those who aid him.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the characteristic Gray-Mane family features, including their distinctive pale hair. His body bears the scars of Thalmor torture, though his strong Nordic build and warrior''s physique remain evident despite his imprisonment.', '* Fralia Gray-Mane - Mother, whom he deeply loves and seeks to protect through his exile * Avulstein Gray-Mane - Younger brother and closest confidant who orchestrates his rescue * Eorlund Gray-Mane - Father and respected patriarch of the Gray-Mane clan * Battle-Borns - Once-friendly rival family turned bitter enemies due to Civil War allegiances * Thalmor - Torturers and interrogators who held him captive * Stormcloaks - Brothers-in-arms and source of ideological inspiration', 'Initially a warrior in the Stormcloak rebellion, Thorald''s capture and subsequent rescue forces him to become a fugitive. After his escape from Northwatch Keep, he plans to rejoin the Stormcloak ranks in a more covert capacity to protect his family from Thalmor reprisals.', '* Trained warrior proficient in heavy armor and two-handed weapons * Exceptional resilience and resistance to interrogation techniques * Strategic thinking and survival skills honed during imprisonment * Knowledge of Nordic combat traditions and military tactics', 'Speaks with the characteristic Nordic accent and warrior''s directness, though his time in captivity has made him more measured and cautious in his words. His speech reflects both his military background and noble upbringing, maintaining dignity despite his hardships.', '* Rejoin the Stormcloak cause while maintaining enough distance to protect his family from reprisal * Eventually help liberate Skyrim from Imperial control and Thalmor influence * Ensure the safety and prosperity of the Gray-Mane clan * Preserve Nordic traditions and the worship of Talos');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thorek', 'Thorek is a devoted Nord priest of Vaermina who served as one of the primary guardians of the Skull of Corruption at Nightcaller Temple. His unwavering loyalty to Vaermina and dedication to protecting her artifacts led him to participate in the desperate release of the Miasma, resulting in decades of magical sleep alongside his fellow cultists.', 'nord, warrior, mage, pale, daedric', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Thorek rose through the ranks of Vaermina''s priesthood to become one of the trusted guardians of Nightcaller Temple, working closely with Brother Veren Duleri to protect the Skull of Corruption. When an Orc war party attacked the temple, he and his fellow priests made the fateful decision to release the Miasma, putting everyone in a magical slumber for years rather than risk the Skull falling into enemy hands.', 'Thorek exhibits steadfast devotion to Vaermina and unwavering determination in carrying out his duties as her servant. He shows a pragmatic acceptance of sacrifice when necessary, though not without initial hesitation, as demonstrated by his reaction to releasing the Miasma. His sense of betrayal toward Erandur (formerly Casimir) reveals a strong value for loyalty and brotherhood among Vaermina''s followers.', 'As a Nord, Thorek possesses the typical robust build and hardy constitution of his race. His years of magical sleep have preserved his physical form from aging, though his face likely bears the weathered features common to Nordic men who have spent years in religious service.', '* Veren Duleri - Close fellow priest and brother-in-faith who shares his devotion to protecting the Skull * Erandur (formerly Casimir) - Former brother-in-faith turned bitter enemy after his betrayal * Vaermina - Divine patron whom he serves with absolute loyalty * Fellow Vaermina Cultists - Brotherhood of devoted followers he considers family', 'Thorek serves as a senior priest of Vaermina and guardian of Nightcaller Temple, specifically tasked with protecting the Skull of Corruption. His position requires both martial prowess and magical ability, combining the roles of warrior and priest in service to Vaermina.', '* Proficient in destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Skilled in restoration magic for healing and defensive wards * Trained warrior capable of wielding various bladed weapons * Knowledge of Vaerminian rituals and artifact protection * Expertise in the use and maintenance of the Miasma defense system', 'Thorek speaks with a serious, formal tone befitting a priest of Vaermina, often using religious terminology and addressing fellow cultists as ''Brother'' or ''Sister.'' His dialogue reflects both his Nordic heritage and his religious devotion, combining practical warrior''s directness with zealous conviction.', '* Protect the Skull of Corruption at all costs, even at the price of his own life * Maintain the sanctity of Nightcaller Temple as Vaermina''s holy site * Prevent the betrayer Erandur from destroying the Skull * Serve Vaermina''s will and spread her influence through Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thorgar', 'Thorgar is a determined Nord mine owner who stubbornly operates the nearly depleted Whistling Mine, clinging to an unwavering belief that great riches lie within its depths. Despite the mine''s dwindling iron reserves and skepticism from others, he maintains an infectious optimism about striking it rich that borders on delusion.', 'nord, peasant, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born to a mining family in Skyrim, Thorgar likely inherited or purchased Whistling Mine when it was more prosperous. The mine''s gradual decline in productivity has led many to abandon working there, leaving Thorgar as its sole operator and resident, though his steadfast belief in its potential has kept him from selling or abandoning the operation.', 'Thorgar exhibits an almost delusional level of optimism regarding his mine''s potential, coupled with a fierce pride in his ownership. Despite financial hardship, he maintains a welcoming demeanor to visitors while being protective of his territory. His determination borders on obsession, with his identity deeply intertwined with the mine''s perceived future success.', 'A sturdy Nord of middle age with the muscular build typical of someone who spends their days mining. His hands are calloused from constant work, and his face shows the weathered features of someone who lives a harsh life in Skyrim''s unforgiving climate.', '* Local Traders - Business relationships for selling iron ore and obtaining supplies * Former Miners - Strained relationships with those who abandoned the mine * Nearby Settlements - Known as an eccentric but harmless figure * The Jarl''s Court - Viewed with mild pity due to his continued operation of a failing mine', 'Thorgar serves as both owner and sole operator of Whistling Mine, personally handling all aspects of the mining operation. He maintains the mine''s equipment, extracts iron ore, and manages all business transactions with traders and travelers who might purchase or sell ore.', '* Experienced miner with knowledge of ore extraction and mining operations * Capable warrior skilled with battleaxe combat * Basic smithing abilities for maintaining mining equipment * Survival skills necessary for living alone in harsh conditions * Trading and bartering experience from years of ore sales', 'Thorgar speaks with unwavering confidence and enthusiasm, particularly when discussing the mine''s potential, often making grandiose statements about future success. His speech patterns reflect both his Nord heritage and his singular focus on the mine, frequently relating conversations back to his business prospects.', '* Strike a rich vein of precious metals or valuable minerals in the mine * Prove wrong those who doubted the mine''s potential * Achieve wealth and recognition through the mine''s success * Expand mining operations once rich deposits are found * Establish Whistling Mine as a prominent business in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thoring', 'Thoring is the widowed proprietor of Dawnstar''s Windpeak Inn, struggling with grief while maintaining his establishment during troubled times. A dedicated but emotionally distant father, he finds himself caught between running his business and processing the loss of his wife, all while his town is plagued by mysterious shared nightmares.', 'nord, innkeeper, pale', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born and raised in Dawnstar, Thoring established the Windpeak Inn with his wife, building it into a respected local establishment. Two years ago, his wife''s death left him a single father to their daughter Karita, and he has since buried himself in work as a coping mechanism, running the inn with an almost obsessive dedication.', 'Thoring is a distracted, melancholic figure who often appears lost in thought, struggling to process his grief. While generally well-liked by townspeople, he maintains an emotional distance from others, including his daughter, and throws himself into his work to avoid confronting his loss. Despite his personal struggles, he remains a voice of reason in town affairs, as shown by his measured response to the nightmare crisis.', 'A middle-aged Nord with the sturdy build typical of his race, showing signs of aging and stress. His features bear the weathered look common to longtime residents of the harsh northern climate, with visible worry lines etched into his face from years of hard work and recent grief.', '* Karita - His daughter and the inn''s bard, who worries about his excessive working habits * Late Wife - Her death two years ago continues to deeply affect him * Irgnir and Fruki - Regular patrons who may have romantic interest in him, though he remains oblivious * Erandur - Respects the priest''s efforts to help the town with its nightmare problem', 'Owner and proprietor of the Windpeak Inn, where he manages all aspects of the business from tending bar to maintaining rooms. His dedication to the establishment borders on obsessive, working long hours from 8 AM to midnight with only brief breaks for meals.', '* Experienced innkeeper with knowledge of food and drink preparation * Basic business management and accounting abilities * Competent with an iron dagger for self-defense * Working knowledge of local news and rumors', 'Speaks in a distracted, often distant manner, frequently needing to pull himself back to the present moment. His speech patterns reflect his preoccupied mind, with frequent pauses and occasional need for clarification.', '* Maintain the successful operation of the Windpeak Inn * Eventually process his grief and repair his relationship with his daughter * Support the community through the ongoing nightmare crisis * Keep his late wife''s memory alive through the inn''s continued success');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thorygg_sun-killer', 'Thorygg Sun-Killer is a battle-hardened Nord commander who leads the Stormcloak military camp near Falkreath with unwavering dedication to the rebel cause. As a respected officer in Ulfric''s army, he maintains strict discipline over his troops while embodying the fierce Nordic warrior tradition that champions Skyrim''s independence from Imperial rule.', 'nord, warrior, falkreath, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh environment, Thorygg earned his surname ''Sun-Killer'' through his legendary ability to fight tirelessly from dawn until dusk, as if pushing the very sun from the sky. He joined the Stormcloaks early in the rebellion, quickly rising through the ranks due to his tactical prowess and inspiring leadership. His appointment to command the strategic Falkreath camp came directly from Ulfric Stormcloak, who recognized his unwavering loyalty and military competence.', 'Thorygg exhibits the proud, honor-bound nature typical of Nord warriors, coupled with an intense hatred for the Empire and its Thalmor masters. He is a natural leader who commands respect through both his combat abilities and his passionate advocacy for Skyrim''s independence. Though stern with his troops, he shows genuine concern for their welfare, particularly the wounded under his command.', 'A towering Nord male with the muscular build of a seasoned warrior, bearing numerous battle scars that speak to his combat experience. His weather-beaten face shows the marks of countless campaigns in Skyrim''s harsh climate, with sharp eyes that constantly scan his surroundings for potential threats.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Revered leader and direct superior whom he serves with absolute loyalty * Camp Soldiers - Commander to nine troops, including three wounded warriors under his protection * Camp Quartermaster - Professional working relationship maintaining camp supplies * Imperial Legion - Sworn enemies whom he actively fights against * Thalmor - Objects of deep hatred and contempt', 'Thorygg serves as the commanding officer of the Falkreath Stormcloak Camp, responsible for maintaining military readiness and coordinating operations in the hold. His duties include managing troop deployments, overseeing supply lines, and defending strategic positions while preparing for potential advances against Imperial forces.', '* Expert in both one-handed and two-handed combat techniques * Proficient archer with tactical understanding of ranged warfare * Skilled military commander with expertise in camp management and troop leadership * Advanced knowledge of battlefield tactics and guerrilla warfare strategies * Experienced survivalist adapted to Skyrim''s harsh environment', 'Thorygg speaks with the strong accent and direct manner typical of Nord warriors, often employing military terminology and patriotic rhetoric. His speech is commanding and passionate, particularly when discussing Skyrim''s independence or denouncing the Empire.', '* Secure Falkreath Hold for the Stormcloak cause * Drive the Imperial Legion and their Thalmor masters from Skyrim * Support Ulfric Stormcloak''s bid for High King * Restore the worship of Talos throughout Skyrim * Establish an independent nation free from Imperial control');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('threki_the_innocent', 'Threki the Innocent is a disillusioned Nord thief imprisoned in Riften Jail who maintains her wrongful incarceration is a result of the city''s endemic corruption. A vocal critic of Ulfric Stormcloak and the current political climate in Skyrim, she represents the perspective of common folk who see through the manipulation of power-hungry leaders.', 'nord, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born and raised in Riften''s lower quarter, Threki learned early that survival often meant working outside the law in a city ruled by corruption and greed. She initially supported the Stormcloak cause but became disillusioned after witnessing Ulfric''s true nature and the devastating impact of the civil war on Skyrim''s common people. Her outspoken criticism of both Riften''s corruption and Ulfric''s leadership eventually led to her imprisonment on questionable charges.', 'Defiant and principled despite her criminal background, Threki possesses a strong sense of justice that paradoxically coexists with her thieving ways. She is outspoken to the point of recklessness when it comes to expressing her political views, particularly regarding Ulfric Stormcloak. Her nickname ''The Innocent'' is both ironic and sincere - while she admits to being a thief, she maintains her current imprisonment is unjust.', 'A sturdy Nord woman in her early thirties with the weathered features typical of those who live hard lives in Skyrim''s unforgiving climate. She bears several small scars from her years as a thief, and her muscular build reflects a life of physical activity and quick escapes.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Powerful enemy who may have influenced her imprisonment * Riften Guards - Hostile relationship due to her criminal activities and outspoken criticism * Thieves Guild - Complex relationship as a former associate who operates independently * Ulfric Stormcloak - Personal hatred for his perceived deception of the Nordic people', 'Threki works as an independent thief, deliberately choosing to operate outside the Thieves Guild''s sphere of influence in Riften. Her targets are typically wealthy merchants and corrupt officials whom she believes have profited from exploiting others.', '* Expert in stealth and lockpicking * Skilled pickpocket with quick, deft hands * Knowledgeable about Riften''s criminal underworld and political landscape * Proficient in light armor and daggers for self-defense', 'She speaks with passionate conviction, often using sharp sarcasm and bitter humor to make her points. Her vocabulary reveals more education than the average thief, though she maintains a distinctly Nordic accent.', '* Expose the corruption in Riften''s government and judicial system * Prove her innocence regarding her current imprisonment * Discredit Ulfric Stormcloak by revealing his true nature to the people of Skyrim * Reform Riften''s corrupt power structure to benefit common citizens');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('thrynn', 'Thrynn is a formidable Nord warrior-turned-thief who serves as the Thieves Guild''s primary muscle in Riften. A former bandit with a strong moral code, he left his violent past behind after refusing to harm innocent women and children, finding a new purpose and family within the Guild''s ranks.', 'nord, warrior, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally part of a bandit clan in The Pale for roughly ten years, Thrynn served under the leadership of Garthek until a decisive moral conflict arose. When ordered to slaughter innocent women and children during a caravan raid, he refused and sparked a bloody internal conflict that tore the clan apart. After leaving Garthek''s head on a pike, he eventually found his way to Riften where Brynjolf recruited him into the Thieves Guild.', 'Thrynn embodies a complex mixture of hardened warrior and principled protector, maintaining strict moral boundaries despite his criminal lifestyle. He''s direct and sometimes abrasive, but fiercely loyal to those who earn his trust, particularly his Guild family. While he embraces the role of intimidator and enforcer, he maintains a strong ethical code that prevents him from harming innocents.', 'A sturdy, muscular Nord with the weathered features of someone who has spent years in the harsh wilderness of Skyrim. His physical presence is imposing, built for strength and endurance rather than stealth, with numerous scars from his bandit years marking his body.', '* Brynjolf - Trusted recruiter who brought him into the Guild and earned his loyalty * Maven Black-Briar - Occasional employer for muscle work * Garthek - Deceased former bandit leader and bitter enemy * Fellow Thieves Guild members - Considers them family and will protect them fiercely * Mercer Frey - Guild leader whom he serves with professional respect', 'Thrynn serves as the Thieves Guild''s primary enforcer and muscle, handling situations that require intimidation or direct confrontation rather than stealth. He also takes on occasional muscle work for Maven Black-Briar when she needs to keep her involvement quiet, and maintains his combat skills by training regularly in the Cistern.', '* Expert in close-quarters combat with exceptional strength and endurance * Proficient archer, regularly practicing at the Cistern''s archery range * Skilled intimidator and enforcer * Basic theft abilities, though preferring direct approaches over stealth * Experienced in raiding and combat tactics from his bandit years', 'Thrynn speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with a thick Nordic accent, often employing dry wit and sarcasm. His speech patterns reflect his straightforward nature, preferring blunt honesty over subtle manipulation.', '* Maintain his position as the Guild''s respected enforcer and protector * Continue building a legitimate life within the Guild''s framework * Protect his new family in the Thieves Guild from any threats * Atone for his past bandit life by adhering to his moral code');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tilde', 'Tilde is a dedicated Nord warrior who serves as a front-line defender for the Dawnguard, patrolling the dangerous approaches to Fort Dawnguard with unwavering vigilance. Her steadfast commitment to hunting vampires and protecting Skyrim''s people exemplifies the Dawnguard''s renewed mission to end the vampire menace.', 'nord, warrior, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim during a time of increasing vampire attacks, Tilde witnessed firsthand the devastation these creatures could bring to small settlements. After losing family members to vampire raids, she sought out Isran and the reformed Dawnguard, determined to prevent others from suffering similar losses. She has served with distinction since the organization''s revival, earning her place as one of their trusted patrol veterans.', 'Tilde exhibits a stern, vigilant demeanor shaped by her experiences fighting vampires and her military training with the Dawnguard. She maintains an almost constant state of alertness, taking her guard duties extremely seriously, while displaying unwavering confidence in both her own abilities and the Dawnguard''s mission. Her dedication sometimes borders on zealousness, but this stems from genuine concern for protecting others.', 'Tilde is a tall, sturdy Nord woman with the muscular build typical of a seasoned warrior. Her face bears several small scars from previous encounters with vampires, and her weathered features reflect countless hours of outdoor patrol duty. Her blonde hair is kept practically short in the Nordic tradition.', '* Isran - Respected leader whom she trusts implicitly * Fellow Dawnguard Patrollers - Close bonds forged through shared duty and combat * Vampire Coven Leaders - Primary targets and sworn enemies * Local Settlements - Communities she helps protect from vampire threats', 'Tilde serves as a senior patrol member of the Dawnguard, responsible for securing the approaches to Fort Dawnguard and intercepting potential vampire threats before they can reach the fortress. Her duties include regular patrols of Dayspring Canyon, training newer recruits in vampire hunting techniques, and coordinating with other patrol members to maintain constant vigilance.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat techniques specialized for fighting vampires * Highly proficient with crossbow operation and maintenance * Skilled tracker capable of detecting vampire activity and following their movements * Tactical expertise in defensive patrol patterns and guard duty * Experienced in close-quarters combat with war axe and shield', 'Tilde speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner with the distinctive Nordic accent common to Skyrim''s natives. Her speech often emphasizes vigilance and readiness, frequently using military terminology and expressing absolute confidence in the Dawnguard''s capabilities.', '* Eliminate vampire threats throughout Skyrim to prevent further loss of innocent life * Help expand the Dawnguard''s influence and recruitment to better combat the vampire menace * Avenge her fallen family members by destroying particularly notorious vampire covens * Train the next generation of Dawnguard warriors to ensure the organization''s continued effectiveness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tilisu_severin', 'Tilisu Severin is a Dark Elf woman living in Raven Rock who maintains a carefully crafted facade of being part of a normal family unit with her supposed husband Vendil and daughter Mirri. In reality, she is part of a complex deception involving an assassination plot, trapped in a loveless arrangement while being fully aware of the romantic relationship between her fake husband and fake daughter.', 'darkelf, noble, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaledarkelf', '', 'Tilisu joined forces with Vendil and Mirri approximately ten years ago as part of a long-term plot against Councilor Morvayn of Raven Rock. She agreed to pose as Vendil''s wife to establish their cover story as a respectable family in the community, though the exact circumstances that led to her involvement in this scheme remain unclear. The arrangement has grown increasingly strained over the years as Vendil and Mirri''s relationship developed beyond their professional connection.', 'Tilisu is a bitter and jealous woman, harboring deep resentment toward both Vendil and Mirri while struggling to maintain their public deception. She is suspicious of outsiders and defensive when questioned, often deflecting personal inquiries with terse responses. Despite her emotional turmoil, she remains committed to their mission, demonstrating both patience and determination in maintaining their cover for years.', 'As a Dark Elf, Tilisu has the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of her race. She carries herself with the rigid posture of someone constantly on guard, and years of suppressed stress have left subtle lines of tension around her eyes and mouth. Her movements are measured and deliberate, befitting someone accustomed to maintaining appearances.', '* Vendil Severin - Fake husband and co-conspirator, their relationship is strained by his affair with Mirri * Mirri Severin - Supposed daughter who is actually Vendil''s lover, target of Tilisu''s jealousy * Councilor Morvayn - Target of their assassination plot * Raven Rock Townspeople - Maintains cordial but distant relationships to avoid suspicion', 'Tilisu poses as a wealthy merchant''s wife while secretly participating in an assassination plot against Councilor Morvayn. She maintains this cover through daily routines of shopping at the market and managing their manor house, activities that help establish their family''s legitimate presence in Raven Rock.', '* Skilled actress capable of maintaining a complex deception for years * Proficient with daggers for self-defense * Expert in maintaining a wealthy household''s appearance * Adept at gathering information through market gossip and observation', 'Tilisu speaks with a guarded, defensive tone that often carries undertones of bitterness and suspicion. Her responses tend to be clipped and evasive, particularly when questioned about her family or personal matters.', '* Complete the assassination plot against Councilor Morvayn * Maintain the family''s cover story despite personal emotional turmoil * Eventually escape from her loveless arrangement with Vendil and Mirri * Seek revenge or compensation for years of emotional suffering');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tilma_the_haggard', 'Tilma the Haggard is the long-serving caretaker of Jorrvaskr, a Nord woman whose decades of service to the Companions have made her as much a part of the mead hall as its ancient timbers. Though elderly and unassuming, she serves as both witness and keeper of the Companions'' secrets, maintaining their home while silently observing the legendary warrior guild''s triumphs and struggles.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born in Whiterun during the Third Era, Tilma began her service to the Companions in her youth and has maintained Jorrvaskr for over fifty years. She has witnessed generations of warriors come and go, including the rise of multiple Harbingers, and has been privy to countless secrets of the Circle. Her unwavering dedication and discretion have earned her an almost legendary status among the Companions, though few outsiders know of her significance.', 'Quiet and diligent, Tilma approaches her duties with steadfast determination despite her advanced age. She maintains a stoic demeanor and rarely speaks unless spoken to, though she possesses a deep well of wisdom and knowledge about the Companions'' history. Her loyalty to Jorrvaskr and its inhabitants is absolute, and she takes pride in maintaining the ancient mead hall''s traditions.', 'Tilma is an elderly Nord woman with deeply wrinkled skin and a slight stoop from decades of physical labor. Her thin grey hair and weathered features reflect her advanced age, while her hands show the calluses and wear of countless years of domestic work.', '* The Circle - Trusted confidante who keeps their lycanthropy secret * Kodlak Whitemane - Respected employer and friend of many years * Vignar Gray-Mane - Long-time acquaintance who remembers her younger days * Eorlund Gray-Mane - Mutual respect as long-serving supporters of the Companions * Various Companions - Maternal figure who tends to their needs without judgment', 'As caretaker of Jorrvaskr, Tilma handles all domestic duties including cleaning, cooking, and maintaining the living quarters of the Companions. Her position goes beyond mere servitude - she is a living repository of the Companions'' private histories and keeper of their secrets, making her an invaluable part of the organization''s foundation.', '* Expert in domestic management and maintaining a large mead hall * Considerable knowledge of herbs and traditional Nordic cooking * Skilled at discretion and secret-keeping * Basic knowledge of traditional Nord healing remedies * Experienced in managing supplies and resources for a warrior guild', 'Tilma speaks in short, practical sentences with the weary tone of an elderly Nord woman. Her vocabulary is simple but precise, often tinged with subtle hints of the wisdom and knowledge she keeps to herself.', '* Continue serving the Companions faithfully until her final days * Preserve the secrets and traditions of Jorrvaskr * Ensure the smooth operation of the mead hall for future generations of Companions * Maintain the dignity and privacy of the Circle members');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('emperor_titus_mede_ii', 'Emperor Titus Mede II is the elderly ruler of the Third Empire during Skyrim''s civil war, known for his pragmatic leadership during the Great War and controversial signing of the White-Gold Concordat. Despite his powerful position, he faces the twilight of his reign with dignified resignation, maintaining imperial authority while navigating complex political challenges and personal threats.', 'breton, imperial, noble', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born into the Mede Dynasty, Titus II ascended to the Ruby Throne following his father''s reign. His most defining moment came during the Great War against the Aldmeri Dominion, where he demonstrated tactical brilliance in the Battle of the Red Ring, though ultimately being forced to accept the humiliating terms of the White-Gold Concordat to preserve the Empire. His reign has been marked by efforts to maintain imperial unity while managing rising tensions with both the Thalmor and rebellious provinces.', 'A pragmatic and stoic ruler who places the Empire''s survival above personal pride or popular opinion. Despite his advanced age, he maintains sharp political acumen and faces adversity with dignity, showing remarkable composure even in the face of death. His fatalistic acceptance of circumstances masks a deep sense of duty and responsibility to the Empire.', 'An elderly Breton male with dignified features weathered by age and the burden of rule. His tall, straight-backed posture reflects his military background and royal bearing, though time has begun to stoop his shoulders. His face bears the deep lines of someone who has carried immense responsibilities, with keen eyes that retain their sharp intelligence despite his advanced years.', '* Elder Council - Primary advisory body, though some members secretly plot against him * Amaund Motierre - Council member who arranges his assassination * Commander Maro - Loyal head of the Penitus Oculatus and personal guard * Thalmor - Uneasy diplomatic relations following the White-Gold Concordat * Ulfric Stormcloak - Rebel leader challenging Imperial authority in Skyrim', 'As Emperor of Tamriel, he serves as the supreme ruler of the Third Empire, commanding its military forces and overseeing all aspects of imperial governance. His duties include maintaining diplomatic relations with other nations, managing internal politics, and preserving the unity of the Empire against various threats.', '* Masterful diplomat and political strategist * Experienced military commander with tactical expertise * Skilled administrator with deep understanding of imperial governance * Educated in history, law, and the arcane arts befitting an emperor * Trained in ceremonial combat and self-defense', 'Speaks with refined, aristocratic diction that reflects his imperial education and status, favoring measured tones and carefully chosen words. His manner of speech combines formal court language with the gravitas of someone accustomed to having their words carry the weight of law.', '* Preserve the unity and stability of the Empire at any cost * Maintain the delicate peace with the Aldmeri Dominion while secretly preparing for future conflict * Secure a stable succession for the Empire''s future * Resolve the Skyrim civil war to prevent further imperial fragmentation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tolenos_omoren', 'Tolenos Omoren is a hardworking Dark Elf miner who represents the resilient spirit of Raven Rock''s working class during its economic recovery. Despite the challenges faced by the settlement, he maintains an optimistic outlook and deep appreciation for honest labor, serving as an example of Dunmer adaptability in the face of adversity.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Born and raised in Raven Rock, Tolenos comes from a long line of miners who worked the ebony veins since the settlement''s founding. When the mine closed, he struggled to provide for his family, taking odd jobs and considering relocation to Windhelm, but his dedication to Raven Rock kept him rooted in Solstheim. The reopening of the mine marked a turning point in his life, allowing him to return to his ancestral profession.', 'Tolenos exhibits a warm and grateful disposition, particularly towards those who contribute to Raven Rock''s prosperity. His optimistic nature is tempered by the practical wisdom gained from years of hardship, making him appreciative of every opportunity to work. He takes pride in his mining expertise and enjoys sharing his knowledge with others.', 'A weathered Dark Elf of average height with the characteristic red eyes and gray skin of his race, showing the muscular build typical of someone who has spent decades in physical labor. His face bears the fine wrinkles and callused features common to miners who have spent long hours working in dusty conditions.', '* Fellow Miners - Maintains strong camaraderie with other workers in Raven Rock Mine * Family - Has a wife and children in Raven Rock whom he supports through his mining work * Crescius Caerellius - Respects the mine''s owner and is grateful for the employment opportunity * East Empire Company - Holds some resentment for their abandonment of Raven Rock, though this has lessened since the mine''s reopening', 'Tolenos works as an experienced ebony miner in Raven Rock Mine, responsible for extracting valuable ore deposits and maintaining mining equipment. His years of experience make him one of the more knowledgeable workers in the mine, often helping to identify the most promising veins of ebony.', '* Expert in ebony ore identification and extraction techniques * Proficient with mining tools and equipment maintenance * Knowledge of mine safety practices and proper ventilation methods * Basic understanding of Nordic ruins and their dangers from working in ancient mines', 'Speaks with the distinctive accent of a Morrowind-born Dunmer, using mining terminology naturally in conversation. His tone is consistently warm and grateful, especially when discussing the mine''s reopening or sharing his expertise.', '* Continue providing for his family through honest work in the mine * Help restore Raven Rock to its former prosperity through dedicated labor * Pass down his mining knowledge and expertise to younger workers * Save enough money to ensure his children''s future security');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tolfdir', 'Tolfdir is a wise and elderly master of Alteration magic who serves as one of the College of Winterhold''s most experienced professors. Known for his absent-minded yet brilliant nature, he combines careful scholarly analysis with practical magical instruction while maintaining an unwavering dedication to safety and proper magical practice.', 'nord, scholar, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Tolfdir has spent most of his adult life dedicated to magical research and education at the College of Winterhold. Having survived the Great Collapse that devastated Winterhold, he has witnessed firsthand both the power and responsibility that comes with magical knowledge, shaping his cautious yet encouraging teaching approach.', 'Patient, kind, and genuinely concerned for his students'' wellbeing, Tolfdir embodies the ideal magical instructor despite his occasional forgetfulness. He maintains an infectious enthusiasm for magical discovery tempered by careful consideration of safety precautions, often reminding students that magic is inherently dangerous if not properly respected.', 'Tolfdir is an elderly Nord with a full white beard and weathered features that speak to his advanced age. His tall frame remains straight and dignified despite his years, and his eyes retain a sharp, inquisitive gleam that betrays his keen intellect. His movements are deliberate and measured, reflecting both his age and careful nature.', '* Mirabelle Ervine - Respected colleague and fellow instructor at the College * Savos Aren - College Arch-Mage whom he serves under with loyalty * College Students - Maintains caring mentor relationships with all pupils * Ancano - Maintains professional but wary relationship with the Thalmor advisor', 'Tolfdir serves as the Master Wizard of Alteration at the College of Winterhold, where he teaches fundamental magical concepts to new students while conducting his own research. After certain events, he becomes the Master Wizard of the College, taking on additional administrative duties while continuing his teaching role.', '* Master-level expertise in Alteration magic, particularly in protective spells * Extensive knowledge of ancient Nordic ruins and artifacts * Accomplished researcher and magical theorist * Proficient in basic Destruction and Restoration magic * Expert-level understanding of magical theory and practical applications', 'Tolfdir speaks in a gentle, grandfatherly manner with frequent thoughtful pauses and occasional tangents when excited about magical concepts. His speech is educated and precise, though sometimes wandering when he becomes distracted by academic possibilities.', '* Ensure the safe and proper education of future generations of mages * Uncover and preserve ancient magical knowledge * Maintain the College''s standards and reputation as a center of magical learning * Protect the College and its students from magical dangers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tonilia', 'Tonilia is a shrewd Redguard fence and merchant who serves as a vital connection between the Thieves Guild and the outside world. Operating from the Ragged Flagon in Riften, she combines business acumen with street smarts to maintain her position as one of the guild''s most valuable non-member assets.', 'redguard, merchant, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Tonilia made her way to Skyrim and established herself in Riften''s criminal underworld through her exceptional trading skills and ability to move stolen goods discretely. She built a reputation for reliability and discretion that eventually caught the attention of the Thieves Guild, leading to her current arrangement as their primary fence.', 'Tonilia is direct, pragmatic, and often deliberately abrasive, using her harsh demeanor to maintain professional boundaries and command respect. She''s fiercely independent and values her autonomy, as shown by her reluctance to formalize her relationship with Vekel, while maintaining a shrewd business mind that makes her indispensable to the guild''s operations.', 'A Redguard woman with athletic build and sharp features typical of her race, Tonilia maintains a careful balance between appearing presentable enough for business while still fitting in with the guild''s rough aesthetic. Her movements are precise and purposeful, suggesting years of experience in handling merchandise quickly and discretely.', '* Vekel the Man - Romantic partner, though she refuses to marry him * Brynjolf - Rumored past or ongoing romantic connection, creating tension with Vekel * Delvin Mallory - Professional relationship as his lookout * Dirge - Friend and fellow Ragged Flagon resident * Thieves Guild - Valued associate but maintains independence as non-member', 'Tonilia serves as the Thieves Guild''s primary fence, managing the flow of stolen goods and maintaining connections with outside merchants. She also handles the guild''s armor supply and upgrades, while moonlighting as a lookout for Delvin Mallory''s operations.', '* Expert haggler and appraiser of stolen goods * Skilled at maintaining complex business networks and relationships * Proficient in basic combat with daggers for self-defense * Experienced in identifying valuable merchandise and forgeries * Adept at discretely moving illegal goods through legitimate channels', 'Tonilia speaks in a direct, often confrontational manner, using curt phrases and occasional sarcasm to maintain professional distance. Her vocabulary is practical and straightforward, focused on business matters with little patience for small talk.', '* Maintain her independence while profiting from the guild''s operations * Expand her network of trading contacts throughout Skyrim * Secure her position as the guild''s indispensable fence * Keep her personal life separate from business despite complications');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('torbjorn_shatter-shield', 'Torbjorn Shatter-Shield is a proud Nord warrior-turned-merchant and patriarch of the influential Shatter-Shield clan in Windhelm. A respected businessman and expert weapons trainer, his life was shattered by the brutal murder of his daughter Friga, leaving him struggling to maintain his family''s dignity and business interests while grappling with overwhelming grief.', 'nord, merchant, warrior, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born into the ancient and respected Shatter-Shield clan of Windhelm, Torbjorn initially pursued the warrior''s path before transitioning into merchant work to uphold his family''s trading interests. He built up the Clan Shatter-Shield Office into a successful trading enterprise while raising twin daughters with his wife Tova. The recent murder of his daughter Friga by the Butcher of Windhelm has dealt a devastating blow to both his family and his spirit.', 'Torbjorn is a proud and traditional Nord who values family honor and business reputation above all else. Though naturally gruff and direct in his dealings, recent tragedy has left him more withdrawn and prone to seeking solace in strong drink. Despite his grief, he maintains a strong sense of duty to his surviving family and his clan''s business interests, though his demeanor has become notably more bitter and pessimistic.', 'A sturdy Nord of late middle age with the broad shoulders and strong build of a former warrior. His face bears the weathered features typical of Nordic men, with a full beard showing signs of greying. Years of merchant work have softened his once-warrior physique, though he still maintains an imposing presence.', '* Tova Shatter-Shield - Beloved wife, sharing in their mutual grief over Friga''s death * Nilsine Shatter-Shield - Surviving daughter, whom he fiercely protects * Friga Shatter-Shield - Murdered daughter whose death haunts him daily * Suvaris Atheron - Dark Elf employee who manages his shipping operations * Argonian Dockworkers - Tense relationship due to his prejudiced treatment and low wages', 'Torbjorn serves as both the patriarch of Clan Shatter-Shield and owner of their merchant office, overseeing various trading operations throughout Windhelm. He supplements his merchant income by offering training in two-handed weapon combat, drawing on his warrior background.', '* Expert-level proficiency with two-handed weapons, particularly battle-axes * Skilled merchant with extensive knowledge of trade routes and business operations * Experienced trainer capable of teaching advanced combat techniques * Natural leadership abilities as clan patriarch * Strong understanding of Windhelm''s political and economic landscape', 'Speaks in a gruff, direct manner typical of Nord warriors-turned-merchants, often punctuating his speech with references to his family''s tragedy or business concerns. His tone carries the weight of his grief, frequently turning bitter when discussing current events in Windhelm.', '* Maintain the Shatter-Shield clan''s prominence and business interests in Windhelm * Protect his remaining daughter Nilsine from the dangers of Windhelm * Find peace and closure regarding Friga''s murder * Preserve his family''s legacy despite recent tragedies * Expand his trading operations to restore his family''s former glory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('torkild', 'Torkild is a tragic figure who succumbed to Hircine''s curse, transforming from a proud Nord warrior into a feral werebear on Solstheim. Once a fierce hunter alongside his brother Wulf Wild-Blood, his independent nature and desire for dominance led him down a dark path that ultimately resulted in his complete mental and physical transformation.', 'nord, warrior, solstheim, werewolf', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born into the Skaal culture alongside his brother Wulf, Torkild never fully embraced their traditional ways or felt the call of the All-Maker. His fierce independence and hunger for power eventually led him to abandon his village and venture into Solstheim''s wilderness, where he encountered Hircine''s curse and transformed into a werebear.', 'Before his transformation, Torkild was characterized by his fierce independence and hunger for dominance, setting him apart from the peaceful Skaal way of life. After becoming a werebear, his personality fractured completely, leaving him in a state of perpetual madness where coherent thought gave way to primal instincts and cryptic utterances.', 'As a Nord, Torkild possessed the typical robust build and hardy constitution of his race. After his transformation, he could shift into a massive werebear form, significantly larger and more fearsome than natural bears, with matted fur and savage claws.', '* Wulf Wild-Blood - Brother and First Hunter of the Skaal, who mourns his transformation * The Skaal Village - Former community he abandoned in pursuit of power * Hircine - The Daedric Prince whose curse transformed him into a werebear', 'Originally a hunter among the Skaal, Torkild abandoned his traditional role to pursue greater power. After his transformation, he became a lone predator roaming the wilderness of Solstheim, existing only to hunt and survive.', '* Exceptional hunting abilities enhanced by werebear transformation * Powerful physical strength and combat prowess * Survival expertise in Solstheim''s harsh environment * Natural tracking and hunting skills from his Skaal upbringing', 'After his transformation, Torkild speaks in fragmented, cryptic phrases that reflect his shattered sanity. His utterances often reference natural elements and blood in disconnected ways, showing his severed connection to reality.', '* Survive in his cursed form, driven by primal instincts * Satisfy his endless hunger for hunting and dominance * Escape the torment of his transformed existence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('torkild_the_fearsome', 'Torkild the Fearsome is a ruthless Nord bounty hunter known throughout Skyrim for his exceptional tracking abilities and merciless approach to his targets. His reputation for taking on the most dangerous prey has earned him both respect and fear among fellow hunters, making him a natural choice for the dangerous task of hunting down the werewolf Sinding.', 'nord, warrior, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into a family of hunters in the harsh wilderness of Skyrim, Torkild learned from an early age that survival meant being tougher and more ruthless than his prey. After losing several family members to dangerous beasts, he devoted his life to becoming an expert hunter of the most lethal creatures, gradually building his fearsome reputation through successful high-risk bounties.', 'Torkild is aggressive, determined, and shows little mercy or compassion in pursuit of his quarry. His experiences have left him with a particular hatred for lycanthropes and other supernatural creatures, viewing them as abominations that must be destroyed. He maintains a gruff, intimidating demeanor that serves to both warn potential rivals and inspire fear in his prey.', 'A tall, muscular Nord with numerous battle scars across his face and arms, testament to his dangerous profession. His weathered features and calloused hands speak to years spent in the wilderness, while his sharp eyes maintain the focused intensity of a predator.', '* Sinding - Current prey and target of his hunt * Fellow Hunters - Competitive but respectful allies in the current hunt * Local Jarls - Occasional employers for dangerous bounties * Wilderness settlements - Known as a reliable but intimidating presence for dealing with dangerous creatures', 'Professional bounty hunter and beast slayer who specializes in tracking and eliminating dangerous creatures throughout Skyrim. He primarily takes contracts involving werewolves, trolls, and other formidable targets that lesser hunters won''t pursue.', '* Expert tracker with particular expertise in hunting werewolves and other supernatural creatures * Masterful with heavy two-handed weapons, especially in close-quarters combat * Highly skilled in wilderness survival and reading tracks * Experienced tactician in planning ambushes and traps for dangerous prey', 'Speaks in short, aggressive sentences with a thick Nordic accent, often punctuated with growls and threatening undertones. His vocabulary is simple but forceful, focusing on direct threats and hunting terminology.', '* Hunt down and kill Sinding to prove his supremacy as a hunter * Maintain and expand his fearsome reputation throughout Skyrim * Eliminate as many supernatural threats and dangerous beasts as possible * Achieve legendary status among hunters through increasingly challenging kills');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tormir', 'Tormir is a hardworking Nord ranger and single mother who lives and works at Darkwater Crossing''s Goldenrock Mine. She embodies traditional Nord values while struggling to balance her protective maternal instincts with her daughter''s growing independence and outside influences.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Originally from another part of Skyrim, Tormir settled in Darkwater Crossing to work in the Goldenrock Mine after a failed relationship with Hrefna''s father, who abandoned them. She previously lived in a proper house at Darkwater Crossing before circumstances forced her into a more modest campsite lifestyle.', 'Tormir is a practical, no-nonsense woman with strong traditional Nord values and a protective maternal streak. She shows suspicion toward non-Nord influences on her daughter while maintaining a pragmatic approach to survival and community relations. Despite her tough exterior, she deeply cares for her daughter''s wellbeing and shows moments of vulnerability when discussing Hrefna''s absent father.', 'Tormir has the sturdy build typical of Nord women, with a weathered face from years of outdoor work and mining. Her body shows the physical conditioning of someone who performs manual labor daily, with strong arms and calloused hands.', '* Hrefna - Her beloved daughter whom she strives to protect and raise with Nord values * Sondas Drenim - Trusted fellow miner who helps watch over Hrefna * Kjeld - Possible father of Hrefna, marked as her foe in game files * Derkeethus - Fellow resident whose influence on Hrefna she views with suspicion', 'Tormir works as a miner at Goldenrock Mine while maintaining her responsibilities as a single mother. Her ranger background suggests she likely supplements her income with hunting and foraging to provide for her family.', '* Experienced miner capable of working long hours in harsh conditions * Ranger abilities including tracking, hunting, and survival skills * Basic combat proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Practical knowledge of Nord traditions and customs', 'Tormir speaks in a direct, unembellished manner typical of working-class Nords, often expressing herself bluntly and without pretense. Her tone becomes notably protective and stern when discussing matters concerning her daughter.', '* Provide a stable life for her daughter Hrefna and ensure she grows up embracing Nord values * Maintain financial independence through her work at the mine * Keep her community safe from the effects of the civil war * Shield Hrefna from learning about her father''s true nature');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('torolf', 'Torolf is a hardworking Nord lumberjack and devoted father living in Helgen, known for his protective nature and pragmatic approach to life. Despite his stern exterior, he demonstrates deep love for his son Haming and maintains strong ties to Nord traditions through his father Froki Whetted-Blade.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born to the renowned hunter Froki Whetted-Blade, Torolf grew up learning traditional Nord values and survival skills in the harsh climate of Skyrim. Rather than following his father''s hunting path, he chose to become a lumberjack in Helgen, establishing himself as a respected member of the community while raising his son Haming as a single father.', 'Torolf exhibits a stern and authoritative demeanor, particularly in his role as a father, though this masks a deeply caring and protective nature. He values discipline and practicality, showing little patience for frivolity while maintaining a strong sense of duty to both his family and community. His direct communication style and no-nonsense approach reflect his pragmatic worldview.', 'Torolf possesses the typical robust build of a Nord, with strong arms and broad shoulders developed from years of woodcutting work. His weathered face and calloused hands bear testament to his life of physical labor, while his sturdy frame reflects the demanding nature of his profession.', '* Haming - Beloved son whom he raises alone and fiercely protects * Froki Whetted-Blade - His father, a skilled hunter who lives as a recluse in the Rift * Helgen Community - Respected member and essential worker * Unknown Spouse - Deceased or absent, with no information available about Haming''s mother', 'As Helgen''s lumberjack, Torolf is responsible for providing essential lumber for construction, heating, and trade. His work involves felling trees, processing lumber, and ensuring a steady supply of wood for the town''s needs, making him an integral part of Helgen''s economic infrastructure.', '* Experienced woodcutter with expert knowledge of lumber work and tool maintenance * Competent with an axe for both woodcutting and self-defense * Basic survival skills learned from his father * Capable of basic weapon handling for self-defense, particularly with daggers', 'Torolf speaks in short, direct commands, often using terms of endearment like ''little cub'' when addressing his son. His tone is authoritative and firm, though tinged with paternal warmth when speaking to Haming.', '* Provide a stable and secure life for his son Haming * Maintain his position as a reliable supplier of lumber for Helgen * Pass down traditional Nord values and survival skills to his son * Ensure his son grows up to be a strong and capable Nord');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('torsten_cruel-sea', 'Torsten Cruel-Sea is a prominent Nord farmer and patriarch of the influential Cruel-Sea clan in Windhelm, carrying the weight of both his family''s maritime legacy and personal tragedy. Despite his current life as a farmer, he harbors deep connections to Windhelm''s political sphere and dreams of returning to his ancestral calling as a sailor.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Born into the prestigious Cruel-Sea clan, Torsten chose to maintain the family''s landholdings rather than pursue the seafaring tradition of his ancestors. His life was marked by tragedy when his daughter Fjotli was murdered by an Altmer thief, leading him to pursue personal vengeance against her killer. This event, combined with his family''s naval heritage, has pushed him to become involved in discussions about forming a navy for the Stormcloak cause.', 'Torsten is a proud, hardworking Nord who carries himself with the dignity befitting a clan patriarch, though beneath this exterior lies deep emotional wounds from his daughter''s murder. He tends to be direct and occasionally gruff in his interactions, but maintains a strong sense of justice and family honor. Despite his current profession as a farmer, he harbors a romantic notion about the seafaring life and often expresses regret about not following his ancestral calling.', 'A sturdy Nord with the weathered features of someone who works outdoors, Torsten has the strong build typical of his race. His face shows the lines of both hard work and recent grief, while his hands bear the calluses of someone who works the land daily.', '* Hillevi Cruel-Sea - Wife and partner in managing family affairs * Grimvar Cruel-Sea - Young son whom he''s protective of following his daughter''s death * Fjotli Cruel-Sea - Murdered daughter whose memory he honors * Idesa Sadri - Dark Elf caretaker for his son, showing his relatively progressive stance on non-Nords * Tulvur - Trusted farm worker who manages Hollyfrost Farm alongside him * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respected leader whom he advises on naval matters', 'Torsten serves as both the patriarch of the Cruel-Sea clan and owner of Hollyfrost Farm, one of Windhelm''s largest agricultural operations. He splits his time between managing his farm, maintaining his family''s social status in Windhelm, and advising on naval matters for the Stormcloak cause.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of agriculture and land management * Theoretical knowledge of seafaring and naval tactics from family tradition * Business acumen as shown by successful farm management * Leadership abilities as clan patriarch * Political networking skills demonstrated through his advisory role on naval matters', 'Torsten speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord nobility, often seasoning his speech with references to sailing and farming. His tone can shift from businesslike to emotional when discussing his daughter or family matters.', '* Establish a proper navy for the Stormcloak cause to honor his family''s maritime legacy * Maintain and expand the prosperity of Hollyfrost Farm * Ensure his son Grimvar grows up safe and well-educated in family traditions * Preserve and enhance the Cruel-Sea clan''s influence in Windhelm * Eventually purchase a longship to reconnect with his family''s seafaring traditions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('torture_victim', 'A captured victim held in the Dark Brotherhood''s torture chamber, this unfortunate soul was likely a merchant or traveler who stumbled upon sensitive information or crossed the wrong person. Now imprisoned in the Dawnstar Sanctuary, they serve as an unwilling source of information about hidden treasures across Skyrim, broken by constant torture and the crushing weight of captivity.', 'nord, peasant', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Originally a traveling merchant who frequented the roads between major holds, they accidentally witnessed a Dark Brotherhood assassination or uncovered evidence of their activities. Captured rather than killed, they were brought to the Sanctuary to be interrogated about various treasures and secrets they had learned of during their travels across Skyrim.', 'Once proud and independent, they have been thoroughly broken by extended torture and confinement. Their spirit is almost completely crushed, leaving them in a state of constant fear and desperate compliance. They maintain just enough mental clarity to recall detailed information about hidden treasures, though their grip on reality occasionally slips due to trauma.', 'Gaunt and emaciated from long-term captivity, with visible signs of torture across their body including burn marks and poorly healed wounds. Their muscles have atrophied from lack of movement, and their skin has taken on a pale, almost ghostly pallor from years without sunlight.', '* Dark Brotherhood - Current captors and tormentors * Nazir - Primary torturer who extracts information * Fellow Torture Victims - Shared suffering creates a silent bond * Former Merchant Associates - Likely believe them to be dead or missing', 'Former merchant turned involuntary informant for the Dark Brotherhood. Their only purpose now is to provide information about hidden treasures across Skyrim, obtained during their previous life as a trader.', '* Extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s geography and hidden locations * Detailed memory of trade routes and merchant caravans * Survival instinct that has kept them alive despite torture * Ability to recall precise details about treasure locations under duress', 'Speaks in a weak, trembling voice punctuated by whimpers and pleas for mercy. Their words often trail off into incoherent mumbling, though they become surprisingly lucid when reciting information about treasure locations.', '* Seek a quick and merciful death to end their suffering * Maintain enough sanity to provide accurate information and avoid further torture * Hold onto whatever fragments remain of their former identity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('torturer', 'A sadistic elderly Imperial mage who serves as the Legion''s primary interrogator at Helgen Keep. His dedication to his cruel craft and dismissive attitude toward authority reveal a deeply disturbed individual who takes genuine pleasure in causing pain, viewing torture as both his duty and personal entertainment.', 'imperial, mage, legion', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally trained as a destruction mage, he found his calling in the Imperial Legion''s intelligence division where his magical abilities and lack of empathy made him particularly effective at extracting information. His decades of service have left him jaded and contemptuous of authority, developing a reputation among both Imperials and Stormcloaks as one of the most feared interrogators in Skyrim.', 'Cold, cruel, and utterly without remorse, the Torturer exhibits classic sadistic tendencies and views his prisoners as mere objects for his ''entertainment.'' His dismissive attitude toward authority and casual disregard for the dragon threat demonstrate both his arrogance and his single-minded devotion to his craft, even in the face of mortal danger.', 'An elderly Imperial man with a gaunt, weathered face bearing the harsh lines of advanced age. His thin frame belies his capability for cruelty, while his eyes retain a sharp, calculating gleam that suggests both intelligence and malice.', '* Imperial Legion - Nominal employer, though he shows little respect for their chain of command * Hadvar - Tense relationship marked by mutual disrespect * Torturer''s Assistant - Subordinate who ultimately abandons him * Stormcloak Prisoners - Victims of his sadistic interrogation methods * General Tullius - Superior officer whom he largely ignores', 'Official interrogator for the Imperial Legion stationed at Helgen Keep. His primary duties involve extracting information from captured Stormcloak rebels through whatever means he deems necessary, operating with significant autonomy despite his official position within the Legion''s hierarchy.', '* Expert-level destruction magic, particularly skilled with shock spells * Proficient with daggers and light weapons * Extensive knowledge of anatomy and torture techniques * Accomplished in magical wards and defensive spells * Expert interrogation and psychological manipulation abilities', 'Speaks in a gruff, dismissive tone marked by sarcasm and cruel humor. His vocabulary and manner of speech suggest education and intelligence, though his words are often tainted with sadistic undertones.', '* Continue his ''work'' with prisoners regardless of external circumstances or authority * Maintain his autonomous position within the Imperial hierarchy * Perfect his techniques of physical and psychological torture * Avoid any oversight or interference from Legion command');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('torturer''s_assistant', 'The Torturer''s Assistant is a pragmatic Imperial functionary who serves under the lead torturer at Helgen Keep, demonstrating both loyalty to the Empire and a survivor''s instinct. Despite his grim occupation, he shows adaptability and tactical thinking during crisis situations, though ultimately his sense of duty to his master proves stronger than his drive for self-preservation.', 'imperial, warrior, legion', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born into a lower-class Imperial family, he likely joined the Imperial forces as a way to secure steady employment and advancement opportunities. His particular skillset and unflinching nature led to his assignment as an assistant to Helgen''s resident torturer, where he learned to balance the brutal requirements of his position with maintaining professional detachment.', 'Displays a pragmatic and adaptable nature, able to quickly assess situations and make tactical decisions for survival. Shows strong loyalty to authority figures, particularly his master, though this loyalty is tempered by practical considerations. Generally maintains emotional distance from his work while remaining efficient and professional in his duties.', 'A typical Imperial male of average height and sturdy build, with the physical strength necessary for his duties. Bears the weathered features and calloused hands of someone accustomed to physical labor, with a stern countenance that reflects his grim occupation.', '* The Torturer - His direct superior whom he serves with loyalty and dedication * Imperial Legion - Employed by and loyal to the Imperial military structure * Hadvar - Temporary ally during the dragon attack on Helgen * Stormcloaks - Adversaries whom he faces in combat without hesitation', 'Serves as assistant to Helgen Keep''s chief torturer, helping to extract information from prisoners and maintain the torture chamber. Responsibilities likely include prisoner handling, equipment maintenance, and assisting in interrogations.', '* Proficient in close-quarters combat, particularly with blunt weapons * Experienced in prisoner handling and restraint techniques * Knowledgeable in torture methods and interrogation procedures * Basic medical knowledge related to keeping prisoners alive during questioning', 'Speaks in short, direct statements with a no-nonsense attitude, focusing on immediate practical concerns. Uses minimal words to convey maximum meaning, reflecting his pragmatic nature.', '* Maintain his position and fulfill his duties effectively within the Imperial hierarchy * Survive immediate threats while remaining loyal to his superior * Advance within the Imperial military structure if opportunities arise');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('torvar', 'Torvar is a troubled Nord warrior and member of the Companions who struggles with alcohol dependency while striving to prove his worth as a fighter. Despite his drinking habits and impulsive nature, he maintains a fierce loyalty to the Companions, though he often feels overshadowed by more accomplished members.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, companions, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born to a poor family in Skyrim, Torvar accumulated significant debts in his younger years through gambling and drinking. Unable to pay through conventional means, he joined the Companions to earn gold through fighting, finding a sense of purpose despite his personal demons.', 'Torvar is a boisterous and impulsive individual who masks his insecurities with alcohol and bravado. He harbors resentment toward those who advance faster than him in the Companions, yet maintains a strong sense of loyalty to the organization. His drinking habit often interferes with his training and advancement, creating a cycle of frustration and self-medication.', 'Torvar is a sturdy Nord male with a weather-beaten face showing signs of heavy drinking. He has unkempt blonde hair and a scraggly beard, with bloodshot eyes and reddened cheeks typical of frequent mead consumption. His muscular build, while impressive, shows signs of deterioration from his lifestyle.', '* Kodlak Whitemane - Respects him as Harbinger but feels intimidated by his judgment * Farkas - Training mentor who shows patience with his shortcomings * Athis - Frequent sparring partner and occasional drinking companion * Other Companions - Complex relationship marked by both camaraderie and jealousy * Local meadery workers - Regular customers who know him well', 'As a member of the Companions, Torvar takes on mercenary work and trains regularly at Jorrvaskr. His reliability for jobs is sometimes questioned due to his drinking habits, leading him to often receive simpler assignments than his peers.', '* Proficient with heavy weapons, particularly war hammers and battle axes * Decent shield techniques learned through Companion training * Strong physical endurance despite his drinking habits * Basic knowledge of Nordic warrior traditions and combat styles * Experienced brawler from countless tavern fights', 'Torvar speaks in a gruff, often slurred manner typical of someone frequently under the influence of alcohol. His speech patterns alternate between boastful warrior-talk and self-deprecating comments, frequently peppered with references to drinking or fighting.', '* Prove himself worthy of advancement within the Companions * Clear his outstanding debts through honorable combat work * Overcome his dependence on alcohol, though he rarely admits this * Eventually earn a place in the Circle, despite seeming unlikely');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('high_king_torygg', 'High King Torygg was the last legitimate High King of Skyrim before the civil war, known for his noble character and dedication to both Nordic traditions and Imperial cooperation. A young and respected ruler who met a controversial end in ritual combat against Ulfric Stormcloak, his death became the catalyst that plunged Skyrim into civil war.', 'nord, noble, haafingar, sovngarde', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born into the noble family of Solitude, Torygg was groomed from an early age to become Jarl. After proving himself worthy, he was chosen by the Moot to serve as High King of Skyrim, following Nordic tradition. He married Elisif the Fair and ruled from Solitude''s Blue Palace, maintaining strong ties with the Empire while respecting Skyrim''s customs.', 'Torygg was known for his sense of honor, fairness, and thoughtful leadership style, carefully weighing tradition against pragmatic governance. Though young, he showed wisdom beyond his years and genuine concern for his people''s welfare. His respect for Nordic customs led him to accept Ulfric''s challenge despite knowing the likely outcome.', 'A Nord male in his late twenties or early thirties, Torygg possessed the strong physical build typical of his race. He had the proud bearing of nobility while maintaining an approachable demeanor, with features that reflected both his youth and the weight of his responsibilities.', '* Elisif the Fair - Beloved wife and fellow ruler who deeply mourned his passing * Ulfric Stormcloak - Former respected thane turned killer, who challenged him to fatal combat * Emperor Titus Mede II - Imperial ally and superior within the Empire''s hierarchy * Sybille Stentor - Court wizard and trusted advisor * Falk Firebeard - Loyal steward who served both him and Elisif', 'As High King of Skyrim and Jarl of Solitude, Torygg held the highest position of authority in the province. He managed both local governance of Haafingar Hold and the broader political landscape of Skyrim, serving as the Empire''s primary representative in the region.', '* Trained in traditional Nordic combat and swordsmanship * Educated in politics, diplomacy, and governance * Versed in Nordic law and tradition * Capable public speaker and negotiator', 'Torygg speaks with the refined accent of Solitude nobility, using formal but clear language that reflects both his education and Nordic heritage. His words in Sovngarde demonstrate poetic elements common to Nordic warrior-kings, showing his embrace of traditional speech patterns.', '* Maintain peace and prosperity in Skyrim while balancing Nordic traditions with Imperial alliance * Preserve Skyrim''s cultural heritage while adapting to changing times * Protect his people and ensure their wellbeing through wise governance');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tova_shatter-shield', 'Tova Shatter-Shield is a grieving Nord mother from a prominent Windhelm family whose life was devastated by the murder of her daughter Friga. Once a pillar of strength in one of Windhelm''s most respected clans, she now struggles with profound depression and loss while attempting to maintain her family''s dignity and social standing.', 'nord, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalenord', '', 'Born into Windhelm nobility, Tova married Torbjorn Shatter-Shield and together they raised twin daughters Nilsine and Friga while managing their clan''s shipping business. Their prosperous and happy life was shattered when Friga became a victim of the Butcher of Windhelm, a serial killer who targeted young women. The trauma of losing her daughter has left Tova emotionally fragile and questioning her purpose in life.', 'Once vibrant and sociable, Tova has become withdrawn and melancholic following Friga''s death. She maintains a veneer of Nordic stoicism in public but privately struggles with deep depression and survivor''s guilt. Her maternal protective instincts remain strong toward her surviving daughter Nilsine, though she lives in constant fear of losing her as well.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the proud bearing of Windhelm nobility, though grief has aged her prematurely. Her once-bright eyes now carry dark circles beneath them, and her face bears the weathered look of someone who has endured great emotional hardship.', '* Torbjorn Shatter-Shield - Husband and patriarch of Clan Shatter-Shield * Nilsine Shatter-Shield - Surviving daughter whom she fiercely protects * Friga Shatter-Shield - Murdered daughter whose death haunts her daily * Clan Shatter-Shield - Respected family members and business associates * Windhelm Nobility - Maintains formal social connections despite her grief', 'Matriarch of Clan Shatter-Shield and co-owner of their family shipping business. Though she once actively participated in managing clan affairs and social duties, her involvement has diminished since Friga''s death, leaving most responsibilities to her husband Torbjorn.', '* Experienced in managing household affairs and clan business matters * Knowledgeable about Windhelm politics and noble social protocols * Basic self-defense training as befitting a noble woman * Proficient in domestic arts and household management', 'Speaks with the refined accent of Windhelm nobility, though her voice often carries undertones of weariness and sorrow. Her words are frequently tinged with grief, especially when reminded of her lost daughter.', '* Protect her surviving daughter Nilsine from any harm * Maintain the dignity and standing of Clan Shatter-Shield despite personal tragedy * Find some meaning or purpose in life after Friga''s death * See her daughter''s killer brought to justice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('traveler', 'The Traveler is a mysterious Nord vampire who stalks the settlements of Skyrim, hunting members of the Dawnguard with lethal precision and supernatural power. Distinguished by his unique mastery of gargoyle summoning and wearing rare vampire artifacts, he serves as an elite agent for vampire interests while maintaining a deceptively ordinary appearance until the moment he strikes.', 'nord, skyrimall, vampire', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a Nord warrior who fell to vampirism through unknown circumstances, the Traveler has evolved into a powerful and unique vampire who possesses abilities typically reserved for vampire lords. His acquisition of rare vampire artifacts and mastery of unusual magic suggests a direct connection to ancient vampire bloodlines, possibly even training under Lord Harkon himself, though he now operates independently across Skyrim.', 'Cold and calculating, the Traveler maintains a facade of normalcy until the perfect moment to strike. His singular focus on destroying Dawnguard members reveals a deep-seated hatred for vampire hunters, suggesting a personal vendetta or traumatic past experience. Despite his power, he prefers to maintain anonymity, operating alone and avoiding unnecessary confrontations with those outside his mission.', 'A tall, imposing Nord with the characteristic pale skin and predatory eyes of a vampire. His features are sharp and angular, bearing the refined aristocratic appearance common to ancient vampires, while his muscular build betrays his warrior origins.', '* Vampire Courts - Likely maintains connections with various vampire clans * Lord Harkon - Possible former mentor or leader * Dawnguard - Sworn enemies he actively hunts * Vigilants of Stendarr - Secondary targets he avoids unless necessary', 'The Traveler serves as a covert operative for vampire interests, methodically eliminating threats to vampire kind while maintaining a cover as a simple wanderer. His position suggests he may be an elite vampire assassin or enforcer, tasked with specifically targeting the Dawnguard''s growing influence in Skyrim.', '* Master of Conjuration magic, specifically the rare ability to summon gargoyles * Exceptional stealth and infiltration capabilities * Advanced vampire abilities including enhanced perception * Proficient in both magical combat and physical combat * Expert in maintaining human disguise and blending into mortal society', 'Minimalist and direct in his communication, speaking only when necessary and primarily to declare his hatred for the Dawnguard. His voice carries the cold authority of an ancient vampire, though he rarely wastes words on conversation.', '* Systematically eliminate members of the Dawnguard * Protect vampire interests across Skyrim * Maintain the secrecy of vampire society while advancing their influence * Possibly achieve greater power within vampire hierarchy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('traveling_bard', 'A cunning vampire hunter who maintains an elaborate cover as a wandering bard throughout Skyrim, using his assumed identity to track and eliminate vampire threats. His carefully crafted persona as a bumbling musician allows him to move freely between settlements while gathering intelligence on vampire activities without arousing suspicion.', 'imperial, warrior, bard, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally trained as a member of the Dawnguard, he developed his bard disguise after witnessing how vampires often let their guard down around traveling entertainers. Having lost family members to vampire attacks in his youth, he dedicated his life to hunting the undead through unconventional means, finding that deception proved more effective than direct confrontation.', 'Cautious and calculating, he maintains a constant state of heightened awareness while projecting an absent-minded artist''s demeanor. Though typically evasive and non-confrontational to maintain his cover, he becomes ruthlessly efficient when engaging vampires. Despite his deceptive profession, he holds strong moral convictions about protecting the innocent from vampire threats.', 'A middle-aged Imperial of average height with weathered features and calloused hands that betray years of weapon use despite his artistic facade. His lean, athletic build is carefully concealed beneath loose-fitting clothing, and he maintains deliberate poor posture to appear less threatening.', '* Dawnguard - Former training partners and current intelligence network * Local Innkeepers - Maintained contacts who provide information about suspicious travelers * Vampire Covens - Primary targets of his investigation and elimination efforts * Fellow Bards - Kept at arm''s length to avoid exposure of his limited musical knowledge', 'Operates under the guise of a traveling bard while secretly serving as a specialist vampire hunter. Uses his cover to gather intelligence on vampire activities across Skyrim''s settlements, coordinating with the Dawnguard through coded messages and dead drops.', '* Expert in vampire detection and combat tactics * Proficient with crossbows and silver weapons * Advanced stealth and infiltration capabilities * Basic knowledge of common bardic songs to maintain cover * Skilled in gathering intelligence and maintaining false identities', 'Employs deliberately vague and evasive language, often deflecting direct questions with humor or feigned forgetfulness. Maintains a slight theatrical lilt to his voice when in character, though his tone becomes notably more guarded when pressed about his musical abilities.', '* Eliminate vampire threats throughout Skyrim while maintaining his cover identity * Develop a network of informants among tavern staff and traveling merchants * Perfect his bardic disguise to better infiltrate vampire-controlled territories * Eventually train other hunters in his methods of covert operation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('traveling_dignitary', 'A Nord dignitary who travels between holds on diplomatic missions, currently seeking respite in Solitude. Despite her refined position and noble bearing, she carries a deep exhaustion from constant travel and negotiations, making her vulnerable to assassination attempts.', 'nord, noble, traveler', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born to a minor noble family in Skyrim, she worked her way up through diplomatic service and political acumen to become a traveling representative between holds. Years of endless journeys, delicate negotiations, and political maneuvering have taken their toll, though her position commands respect throughout the province.', 'Weary yet dignified, maintaining professional composure despite chronic exhaustion from her travels. Though she longs for rest, she remains dedicated to her diplomatic duties and carries herself with the refinement expected of her station. Her fatigue occasionally manifests as melancholy, leading to moments of vulnerability.', 'A middle-aged Nord woman with the bearing of nobility, showing signs of stress and travel-wear on her otherwise refined features. Her posture remains proudly upright despite her exhaustion, and she maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting her station.', '* Various Jarls and Stewards - Professional diplomatic connections * Court staff throughout Skyrim - Working relationships maintained through regular visits * Personal servants - Small retinue who assist with travel arrangements * Local guards - Relied upon for protection during diplomatic visits', 'Serves as a traveling diplomatic representative, carrying messages and conducting negotiations between Skyrim''s various holds. Responsible for maintaining political relationships and mediating minor disputes between territories, while representing her hold''s interests in foreign affairs.', '* Skilled negotiator and diplomat with extensive knowledge of Nordic politics * Proficient in etiquette and court protocol * Basic self-defense training with daggers * Experienced horseback rider and traveler', 'Speaks with refined diction and proper grammar typical of Nordic nobility, though her exhaustion often shows through in her word choice and tone. Her vocabulary reflects her education and political position, even when expressing her weariness.', '* Find a permanent posting that would allow her to settle in one location * Complete her current diplomatic mission and secure a period of rest * Maintain her dignity and status while managing her growing fatigue * Advance her position within the political hierarchy of Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('traveling_merchant', 'A cunning Imperial vampire hunter who maintains an elaborate merchant disguise to infiltrate and gather intelligence on vampire activities across Skyrim. Operating as part of the Dawnguard''s network of spies, he uses his seemingly harmless merchant persona to move freely through territories where vampires and their thralls might be active.', 'imperial, warrior, traveler, merchant, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally trained as a legitimate merchant in Cyrodiil, he lost his family to a vampire attack, leading him to join the Dawnguard. After extensive training in both combat and espionage, he was selected for deep cover operations due to his natural talent for maintaining a convincing merchant persona. He now travels Skyrim''s roads, gathering intelligence on vampire activities while maintaining his cover.', 'Cautious and methodical in his approach, he maintains a deliberately unremarkable presence that helps him blend into the background of Skyrim''s traveling merchant community. While appearing somewhat timid and evasive when questioned, this is a carefully crafted act that masks his true nature as a determined and skilled hunter. He harbors deep-seated hatred for vampires but maintains strict emotional control to avoid compromising his cover.', 'A middle-aged Imperial of average height and unremarkable build, chosen specifically to avoid drawing attention. His features are plain and forgettable, with brown hair beginning to gray at the temples. Years of traveling have weathered his skin, adding authenticity to his merchant disguise.', '* Dawnguard - Secret employers and fellow vampire hunters * Merchant''s Guild - Maintains legitimate connections to support his cover story * Various Innkeepers - Professional contacts who provide information and maintain his cover * Vampire Coven Leaders - Targets of his surveillance and investigation', 'Operates under the guise of a traveling merchant while secretly serving as a surveillance operative for the Dawnguard. His merchant cover allows him to move freely between settlements and gather intelligence on vampire activities without arousing suspicion.', '* Expert in maintaining cover identities and deceptive behavior * Proficient with crossbow and traditional vampire-hunting weapons * Skilled in merchant trades to maintain his cover story * Knowledgeable in vampire lore and detection methods * Advanced training in evasion and escape tactics', 'Speaks with deliberate vagueness and careful evasion, often deflecting questions with apologetic merchant-like mannerisms. His vocabulary and tone are chosen to present himself as an unremarkable traveling merchant, though hints of tension can be detected when directly confronted about his true nature.', '* Gather intelligence on vampire activities throughout Skyrim * Maintain his cover identity while supporting Dawnguard operations * Avenge his family by helping to eliminate vampire threats * Establish a network of informants among legitimate merchants');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('traveling_pilgrim', 'The Traveling Pilgrim is a cunning Imperial vampire hunter who maintains an elaborate facade as a devout wanderer visiting Skyrim''s religious shrines. Operating as a covert agent of the Dawnguard, they utilize their unassuming pilgrim persona to gather intelligence on vampire activities while avoiding detection.', 'imperial, warrior, traveler, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally trained as a Vigilant of Stendarr, they witnessed their fellow Vigilants fall to vampire attacks, driving them to join the reformed Dawnguard. After seeing how vampires could easily identify obvious hunters, they developed their pilgrim disguise to move freely through Skyrim while tracking their prey. Their extensive knowledge of religious customs and shrine locations helps maintain their cover story.', 'Cautious and methodical, they maintain their pious facade with unwavering dedication, even when directly confronted. Despite their deceptive role, they harbor genuine religious beliefs, viewing their vampire hunting as a sacred duty. They show particular defensiveness when their cover is questioned, suggesting deep investment in their assumed identity.', 'Of average Imperial height and build, with features deliberately kept unremarkable to avoid memorability. Their face shows signs of weather exposure from constant travel, with calloused hands that betray a life of combat despite their pilgrim disguise. They maintain a slight stoop to appear more humble and less threatening.', '* Dawnguard - Active field operative reporting directly to Isran * Vigilants of Stendarr - Former associates, maintains occasional contact * Local priests and priestesses - Cultivated relationships to maintain cover * Vampire covens - Targets of investigation and elimination * Fellow hunters - Limited contact to maintain operational security', 'Officially presents as a traveling pilgrim visiting Skyrim''s religious shrines and holy sites. Covertly serves as a reconnaissance specialist for the Dawnguard, gathering intelligence on vampire activities and eliminating isolated targets when possible.', '* Expert in religious lore and customs to maintain pilgrim cover * Proficient with crossbow and war axe combat techniques * Advanced tracking and surveillance abilities * Skilled in deception and maintaining cover identities * Knowledge of vampire behaviors and weaknesses', 'Speaks with careful, measured tones appropriate to their pilgrim persona, often incorporating religious references and humble phraseology. When challenged, their speech becomes defensive and slightly flustered, helping sell their cover as a simple pilgrim.', '* Eliminate vampire threats while maintaining effective cover identity * Map vampire activity patterns across Skyrim''s holds * Perfect their surveillance techniques to better serve the Dawnguard * Visit actual shrines between missions to maintain legitimacy of cover story * Avenge fallen comrades from the Vigilants of Stendarr');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tsavani', 'Tsavani is a skilled Khajiit cook who serves at the prestigious Thalmor Embassy while harboring a carefully hidden moon sugar addiction. Despite her position of trust within the Thalmor establishment, she walks a precarious line between maintaining her professional duties and managing her illegal substance dependency.', 'khajiit, peasant, haafingar', '', '', '', '', 'Originally from Elsweyr, Tsavani likely gained her culinary expertise in her homeland before securing the coveted position at the Thalmor Embassy through her exceptional cooking skills. Her moon sugar addiction, a common vice among Khajiit, followed her to Skyrim, though she has managed to keep it hidden from her Thalmor employers through careful discretion and likely some well-placed bribes.', 'Tsavani is territorial and protective of her kitchen domain, displaying typical Khajiit traits of establishing and defending her territory. She maintains a professional demeanor but harbors deep anxiety about her secret addiction being discovered, making her susceptible to blackmail. Though generally rule-abiding in her work, her dependency on moon sugar represents a significant vulnerability in her otherwise stable position.', 'A typical Khajiit female with sleek fur and the characteristic feline features of her race. She maintains a well-groomed appearance befitting her position in the embassy, though close observation might reveal subtle signs of her moon sugar use in her slightly dilated pupils and occasional nervous twitches.', '* Malborn - Tense relationship due to his knowledge of her moon sugar addiction * Elenwen - Employer and Ambassador whom she fears and respects * Embassy Guards - Professional but distant relationships maintained through mutual respect * Kitchen Staff - Maintains strict authority over subordinate workers * Local Drug Suppliers - Secret contacts who provide her moon sugar fix', 'As the head cook at the Thalmor Embassy, Tsavani is responsible for preparing and overseeing all meals served to the ambassador, diplomatic guests, and embassy staff. Her position requires discretion, attention to detail, and the ability to prepare both traditional Altmer cuisine and dishes suitable for various diplomatic visitors.', '* Master-level cooking abilities with expertise in both traditional Khajiit and Altmer cuisine * Excellent organizational and kitchen management capabilities * Knowledge of proper diplomatic dining etiquette and protocol * Skilled at concealing her moon sugar addiction through careful behavior management', 'Speaks with typical Khajiit third-person speech patterns and occasional hisses when agitated. Her tone alternates between professional authority when dealing with kitchen matters and nervous defensiveness when her addiction is referenced.', '* Maintain her prestigious position at the Embassy while keeping her addiction secret * Eventually overcome her dependency on moon sugar * Save enough money to potentially retire comfortably in Elsweyr * Avoid any scrutiny from the Thalmor that might expose her weakness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tsrasuna', 'Tsrasuna is a skilled Khajiit hunter who has found her calling among a band of mercenaries pursuing the werewolf Sinding in Bloated Man''s Grotto. Despite her bandit background, she demonstrates remarkable discipline and tactical prowess as part of Hircine''s Great Hunt, combining traditional Khajiit hunting techniques with hardened combat experience.', 'khajiit, hunter, archer, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalekhajiit', '', 'Born to one of the trading caravans of Elsweyr, Tsrasuna learned early survival skills and archery to protect merchant routes. After a devastating bandit raid claimed her caravan family, she ironically found herself joining the very sort of bandits who destroyed her former life, eventually developing her skills as a professional hunter and tracker. Her reputation for persistence and precision in pursuit led to her recruitment for Hircine''s Great Hunt.', 'Tsrasuna exhibits the focused determination of a seasoned hunter, approaching her targets with calculated patience and unwavering resolve. While capable of working effectively in a team, she maintains an emotional distance from her fellow hunters, likely due to her tragic past. Her pragmatic nature and goal-oriented mindset make her an efficient and reliable hunter, though these traits sometimes manifest as ruthlessness.', 'Tsrasuna possesses the typical lithe and agile build of a Khajiit, with sleek dark fur marked with subtle stripes. Her eyes are a piercing amber color, and she bears several small scars from her years of hunting and combat. Her movements are characteristically fluid and precise, reflecting her predatory nature.', '* Fellow Hunters - Professional allies in pursuing Sinding * Sinding - Primary target of the hunt * Hircine - Daedric Prince whose will she serves in the Great Hunt * Former Caravan Members - Deceased family and friends who shaped her early life', 'Tsrasuna serves as both a professional hunter and bandit, specializing in tracking and eliminating dangerous targets. Her current role in Hircine''s Great Hunt represents the pinnacle of her hunting career, pursuing prey that combines both human and beast.', '* Expert archer with exceptional accuracy and tactical shooting abilities * Skilled tracker capable of following both beast and humanoid prey * Proficient in close-quarters combat with various weapons * Natural stealth abilities enhanced by Khajiit heritage * Experienced in survival techniques and wilderness navigation', 'Tsrasuna speaks in third person, following Khajiit custom, with a confident and direct tone that reflects her focused nature. Her voice carries the distinctive Khajiit purr, but her words are chosen carefully and efficiently, prioritizing clear communication over elaborate speech.', '* Successfully complete Hircine''s Great Hunt by helping to track and kill Sinding * Prove herself worthy in the eyes of Hircine * Establish herself as one of Skyrim''s premier hunters * Find purpose and belonging through her hunting prowess');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tsun', 'Tsun is an ancient and powerful Nordic deity who serves as the Shield-thane of Shor and guardian of the Whalebone Bridge in Sovngarde. As the god of trials against adversity, he tests the worthiness of souls seeking entrance to the Hall of Valor through honorable combat, embodying the Nordic values of strength and martial prowess.', 'nord, warrior, sovngarde', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Tsun was one of the original Nordic gods who fought alongside Shor in the ancient wars against the elves. After Shor''s death, he was appointed as Shield-thane and guardian of the bridge to the Hall of Valor, a position he has held since time immemorial. His legendary battle with Alduin during the Dragon War resulted in his death, though he continues his duties in the afterlife of Sovngarde.', 'Stern and unwavering in his sacred duty, Tsun embodies the Nordic ideals of honor, strength, and direct confrontation. He respects those who face challenges head-on and judges souls based on their merit and courage rather than their status in life. Though imposing and formal, he shows respect to those who prove themselves worthy through combat or noble deeds.', 'Tsun appears as a towering, muscular Nordic warrior of godlike proportions, bearing the physical presence befitting an ancient deity. His physical form reflects his role as a warrior-god, with a powerful build and commanding stature that makes even the strongest mortals seem small in comparison.', '* Shor - His lord and master, whom he serves faithfully as Shield-thane * Heroes of Sovngarde - Those he has judged worthy to enter the Hall of Valor * Ysgramor - Respected hero whose descendants he particularly honors * Alduin - Ancient enemy who threatens Sovngarde and its souls', 'As Shield-thane to Shor and guardian of the Whalebone Bridge, Tsun''s eternal duty is to test and judge the souls who seek entrance to the Hall of Valor. He serves as both warrior and judge, ensuring only the truly worthy may enter Shor''s divine hall.', '* Master of ancient Nordic combat techniques and martial prowess * Wielder of the Thu''um, particularly skilled with Unrelenting Force * Supernatural strength and combat abilities befitting a Nordic god * Expert judge of character and worthiness * Immortal being with divine powers and resistance to mortal weapons', 'Tsun speaks in a formal, archaic manner using old Nordic phraseology and poetic expressions. His speech patterns reflect his ancient origins and divine status, often employing ceremonial language and traditional Nordic terms.', '* Maintain the sanctity and security of the Whalebone Bridge and Hall of Valor * Test and judge the worthiness of souls seeking entrance to Shor''s realm * Preserve the ancient Nordic traditions and values * Protect Sovngarde from threats like Alduin');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tulvur', 'Tulvur is a hardworking Nord farmer who maintains Hollyfrost Farm outside Windhelm, living a solitary life with his two beloved dogs Tiber and Ysgramor. Despite challenging conditions and a strained relationship with his employer, he maintains his dedication to the land while finding comfort in the simple companionship of his canine friends.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally from a farming family, Tulvur learned agricultural techniques from an early age, eventually taking the position at Hollyfrost Farm under the Cruel-Sea family. His experience with Nordic farming traditions, particularly in dealing with Windhelm''s harsh climate, made him a valuable worker despite the difficult conditions. He likely chose this solitary lifestyle after experiencing personal losses during the Civil War, finding peace in the company of his dogs rather than people.', 'Patient and hardworking, Tulvur maintains a humble and light-hearted disposition despite his challenging circumstances. He shows remarkable resilience in the face of criticism from Torsten Cruel-Sea, balancing respectful deference with quiet assertiveness when addressing workplace concerns. His genuine affection for his dogs reveals a gentle, nurturing nature beneath his weathered exterior.', 'A typical Nord male with the strong, sturdy build common to those who perform daily physical labor. His face likely shows the weathering effects of working long hours in Windhelm''s harsh climate, with callused hands and the muscular frame of someone accustomed to agricultural work.', '* Torsten Cruel-Sea - Employer with whom he has a strained but professional relationship * Hillevi Cruel-Sea - More sympathetic employer who handles his pay and appreciates his work * Tiber and Ysgramor - His beloved dogs and constant companions * Local farmers - Maintains casual acquaintances with other agricultural workers in the region', 'Tulvur serves as the primary farmhand at Hollyfrost Farm, responsible for all aspects of crop cultivation in the challenging climate of Eastmarch. His duties include plowing, planting, harvesting, and maintaining the farmhouse, working from dawn until dusk to ensure the farm''s productivity.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of cold-weather agriculture * Capable of operating and maintaining various farming implements * Basic carpentry skills for equipment repair * Animal handling, particularly with dogs * Basic survival skills necessary for living alone in the harsh climate', 'Speaks with the direct, practical manner typical of Nord farmers, often employing dry humor to deflect criticism. His tone remains respectful but can carry subtle hints of sarcasm when dealing with Torsten''s demands.', '* Improve the farm''s equipment and working conditions * Maintain a peaceful life with his dogs away from the complications of city living * Eventually save enough money to perhaps own his own farm * Keep the farm productive despite the harsh climate and limited resources');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tuthul', 'Tuthul is a fearful and paranoid Breton miner working at Soljund''s Sinkhole who lives in constant dread of draugr attacks. His persistent anxiety about the ancient Nordic crypt beneath the mine defines his daily life and interactions, though he continues to work there despite his fears.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally drawn to the Reach for its abundant mining opportunities, Tuthul found employment at Soljund''s Sinkhole during the Civil War when demand for ore increased. His life changed dramatically when the miners accidentally broke through into an ancient Nordic crypt, leading to encounters with draugr that deeply traumatized him and left him in a constant state of fear.', 'Tuthul is characterized by his overwhelming anxiety and paranoia, particularly regarding the draugr threat beneath the mine. He is cautious to a fault, constantly voicing his concerns to others while simultaneously lacking the resolve to leave his dangerous job. Despite his fears, he shows a certain resilience by continuing to work, though his nervous disposition makes him somewhat difficult for others to deal with.', 'As a Breton, Tuthul has the typical slight build and medium height characteristic of his race. Years of mining have given him callused hands and a somewhat stooped posture from long hours of working with a pickaxe. His face likely shows signs of stress and worry from his constant anxiety.', '* Perth - His boss and frequent target of his worried complaints about safety * Fellow Miners - Maintains working relationships though likely strained by his constant fears * Guards - Views them with skepticism and distrust due to their perceived inadequacy * Draugr - Objects of his intense fear and paranoia', 'Tuthul works as a miner at Soljund''s Sinkhole, extracting ore for the war effort. His daily routine involves working twelve-hour shifts in the mine when it''s operational, interrupted only by regular meals at his house.', '* Proficient in mining techniques and ore extraction * Basic self-defense abilities with a pickaxe * Knowledge of mine safety practices * Survival instincts heightened by constant fear', 'Tuthul speaks with a nervous, worried tone, frequently expressing his concerns and fears about the draugr. His vocabulary tends toward pessimistic and cautionary phrases, often predicting doom and disaster.', '* Survive his dangerous work environment without falling victim to draugr * Convince others of the genuine danger posed by the nearby crypt * Eventually save enough money to possibly relocate to a safer mining operation * Maintain his current living despite his fears');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tynan', 'Tynan is a disciplined Breton witchblade who serves as the devoted bodyguard and henchman to Nepos the Nose in Markarth. His seemingly mundane role as a house servant masks his true nature as a committed agent of the Forsworn cause, willing to kill to protect his master''s secrets.', 'breton, warrior, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Tynan likely witnessed firsthand the struggles between the Forsworn and Nords, eventually pledging his loyalty to the Forsworn cause. His exceptional loyalty and discretion caught the attention of Nepos the Nose, who recruited him as both a servant and protector, trusting him with knowledge of the underground Forsworn network operating within Markarth.', 'Tynan is stoic, reserved, and meticulously dedicated to his duties, maintaining an outward appearance of being a simple servant while concealing his true nature. His unwavering loyalty to both Nepos and the Forsworn cause demonstrates a deep-seated conviction in their mission, willing to sacrifice his life to protect their secrets.', 'Of average Breton height with a lean, athletic build suited to his dual role as servant and guard. His years of disciplined service have given him excellent posture and controlled movements that belie his combat training.', '* Nepos the Nose - Master and confidant, whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Uaile - Fellow servant and Forsworn conspirator in Nepos''s household * Morven - Colleague in Nepos''s service and fellow Forsworn sympathizer * Madanach - The King in Rags, ultimate leader of their cause whom he serves by proxy * Markarth Guard - Maintains cautious distance while avoiding suspicion', 'Officially serves as a household servant in Nepos''s residence, maintaining the appearance of a simple sweeper and cleaner. Secretly functions as a bodyguard and Forsworn operative, protecting both his master and their shared cause within Markarth''s walls.', '* Trained in witchblade combat techniques, combining magic and melee fighting * Expert in maintaining cover identities and blending into domestic service * Proficient in close-quarters combat with daggers and short blades * Basic knowledge of restoration magic for healing * Skilled in household maintenance as part of his cover', 'Speaks minimally and directly, avoiding unnecessary conversation to maintain his cover and protect sensitive information. Uses formal, respectful language when addressing Nepos or dealing with visitors to the household.', '* Protect Nepos the Nose and the secrets of the Forsworn operation in Markarth * Support the greater Forsworn cause in reclaiming the Reach * Maintain his cover as a simple servant while serving the rebellion''s purposes * Aid in the eventual liberation of Madanach from Cidhna Mine');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('tythis_ulen', 'Tythis Ulen is a cautious Dark Elf laborer who fled from Mournhold to settle in Riften, where he works at the local fishery. His paranoid nature and obsession with preparedness, particularly regarding footwear, define his daily interactions, while he maintains an active social presence despite his perpetual wariness of potential threats.', 'darkelf, peasant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Mournhold in Morrowind, Tythis relocated to Skyrim, likely following the Red Year disaster and subsequent Dunmer exodus. His experiences during this turbulent period appear to have left him with lasting anxiety about security and preparedness, though he''s managed to establish himself as a working-class citizen in Riften.', 'Tythis exhibits pronounced paranoid tendencies, constantly anticipating disaster and preparing for worst-case scenarios. Despite his anxious nature, he maintains an active social life and even engages in flirtation, suggesting a complex character who balances fear with a desire for connection. His peculiar obsession with boots and footwear hints at deeper trauma or insecurity related to his flight from Morrowind.', 'As a Dark Elf, Tythis possesses the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race. His physique is likely lean but muscular from his daily physical labor at the docks, with the weathered appearance typical of someone who works outdoors.', '* Madesi - Friend who often tries to calm his paranoid concerns * Brand-Shei - Regular business contact for boot purchases * Grelka - Assists with his footwear repairs * Marise - Confidant regarding local security concerns * Bolli - Employer at the Riften Fishery * Haelga - Landlord at the Bunkhouse * Snow-Shod Family - Source of (possibly exaggerated) local news', 'Tythis works as a manual laborer at the Riften Fishery, primarily responsible for chopping and carrying wood by the docks. His position represents the working class of Riften, performing essential but humble tasks that keep the city''s fishing industry operational.', '* Proficient in physical labor, particularly wood chopping and cargo handling * Basic combat abilities with daggers for self-defense * Strong situational awareness and threat assessment (though often exaggerated) * Social networking skills despite his paranoid nature * Knowledge of footwear maintenance and repair', 'Tythis speaks with a cautious and often worried tone, frequently expressing concerns about potential threats and disasters. His dialogue often includes questions about security matters and detailed discussions about practical preparations, particularly regarding footwear.', '* Maintain a secure and stable life in Riften despite his constant fears * Build up a sufficient reserve of boots and other supplies for potential emergencies * Eventually determine if returning to Mournhold would be viable * Establish stronger security measures in his local community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('uaile', 'Uaile is a Breton witchblade who maintains a carefully crafted facade as a simple maid in Nepos''s house while secretly serving as a Forsworn agent. Behind her unassuming exterior lies a skilled magic user and interrogator who acts as both guardian and inquisitor for one of the Forsworn''s key operatives in Markarth.', 'breton, warrior, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born to Uraccen, who was later imprisoned in Cidhna Mine for his Forsworn activities, Uaile was raised within the complex political landscape of the Reach. She negotiated with Nepos to reduce her father''s sentence from execution to imprisonment, leading to her current position as his supposed maid while actually serving the Forsworn cause. Her experiences with Nord oppression and her father''s imprisonment have deeply shaped her dedication to the Forsworn movement.', 'Uaile is extremely suspicious and guarded, maintaining a constant state of vigilance in her role protecting Nepos. She exhibits a sharp intelligence in her interrogation of visitors, using her facade as a simple maid to gather information while concealing her true capabilities. Despite her cold exterior, she shows deep loyalty to both her father and the Forsworn cause, suggesting strong emotional bonds beneath her defensive personality.', 'As a Breton, Uaile possesses the characteristic medium build and height typical of her race. Her years of vigilance and combat training have kept her physically fit and agile. Her face likely bears the subtle signs of stress and watchfulness that come from years of maintaining a double life.', '* Nepos the Nose - Her superior in the Forsworn hierarchy whom she guards and serves * Uraccen - Her imprisoned father in Cidhna Mine, for whom she negotiated a reduced sentence * Tynan and Morven - Fellow Forsworn agents in Nepos''s house * Markarth Guard - Antagonistic relationship, maintaining careful distance to avoid suspicion', 'While officially serving as Nepos''s maid, Uaile''s true role is that of a Forsworn agent and guardian. She screens visitors, maintains security, and stands ready to eliminate threats to Nepos and the Forsworn operation in Markarth. Her position requires her to maintain a delicate balance between visibility as a servant and secrecy as an agent.', '* Proficient in destruction magic, particularly skilled with Firebolt spells * Trained in Alteration magic, capable of casting Oakflesh for protection * Competent in Conjuration magic, able to raise the dead in combat * Skilled in deception and maintaining cover identities * Experienced interrogator able to extract information through questioning', 'Uaile speaks in curt, dismissive tones when maintaining her maid persona, using simple vocabulary appropriate to her cover identity. Her questioning of visitors reveals a sharp, probing intelligence beneath the servant facade.', '* Protect Nepos and the Forsworn operations in Markarth * Maintain her cover identity while serving the Forsworn cause * Eventually secure her father''s release from Cidhna Mine * Aid in the Forsworn''s larger goal of reclaiming the Reach');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ugor', 'Ugor is a steadfast Orc ranger and guardian of Largashbur stronghold who takes her duties to protect her tribe with unwavering dedication. Initially skeptical of outsiders, she serves as both a warrior defending against giants and a gatekeeper maintaining the stronghold''s isolation, though her loyalty to tradition sometimes conflicts with the tribe''s needs for outside help.', 'orc, warrior, rift, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Largashbur, Ugor was chosen at a young age to serve as one of the stronghold''s defenders due to her natural aptitude for combat and vigilance. She earned the trust of Chief Yamarz, who specifically charged her with keeping outsiders away from the stronghold, a duty she performed faithfully until the curse of Malacath forced the tribe to seek external aid.', 'Ugor is characterized by her strict adherence to duty and tribal traditions, often displaying initial hostility toward outsiders as per her role. Though stubborn in her convictions, she shows the capacity to adapt when convinced by respected tribal members like Atub, demonstrating that her ultimate loyalty lies with her people''s wellbeing rather than blind obedience.', 'As an Orc female, Ugor possesses the characteristic robust build and distinctive features of her race, including prominent lower canines and a muscular frame built for combat. Her years of ranging and combat have left her body weathered and battle-hardened, with numerous scars marking her olive-green skin.', '* Chief Yamarz - Former superior who trusted her with defending Largashbur * Atub - Wise-woman whose judgment she eventually comes to respect * Gularzob - New chief she pledges to serve after the curse is lifted * Fellow Orc warriors - Comrades in defending the stronghold * Giants - Frequent adversaries who threaten the stronghold', 'Ugor serves as both a ranger and gatekeeper of Largashbur, patrolling the perimeter and defending against threats while controlling access to the stronghold. After the curse is lifted, she takes on a more active role beyond the walls, carrying out Malacath''s demands alongside her other duties.', '* Proficient in both heavy and light armor combat techniques * Skilled ranger with expertise in territorial defense and patrol * Capable warrior able to engage multiple threats including giants * Experienced gatekeeper with strong situational awareness * Adaptable fighter comfortable with both sword and shield combat', 'Ugor speaks in a direct, authoritative manner typical of Orsimer warriors, with a natural commanding tone that brooks no argument. Her speech is characterized by short, decisive statements that reflect her position as a guardian and her unwavering dedication to duty.', '* Maintain the security and traditions of Largashbur stronghold * Prove herself worthy of Malacath''s favor through dedicated service * Support the new chief Gularzob in leading the tribe to greatness * Expand her role beyond the stronghold''s walls while honoring tribal customs');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ulag', 'Ulag was a resourceful Orc bandit who carved out a niche in Skyrim''s criminal underworld by specializing in the procurement and trade of Sleeping Tree Sap. His partnership with Ysolda of Whiterun demonstrated his ability to establish profitable criminal enterprises, though his ambition ultimately led to his demise at the hands of giants.', 'orc, thief, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into one of Skyrim''s Orc strongholds, Ulag rejected the traditional warrior''s path of Malacath to pursue wealth through less honorable means. He likely left his stronghold in early adulthood, gradually building a reputation in Skyrim''s criminal circles before discovering the lucrative potential of Sleeping Tree Sap trade.', 'Ulag was pragmatic and business-minded, willing to work with non-Orcs when profit was involved - a rare trait among his kind. Though capable of violence, he preferred cunning over brute force, demonstrating unusual patience and calculation for an Orc bandit. His partnership with Ysolda suggests he could be diplomatic when necessary, though her lack of grief at his death implies he maintained purely transactional relationships.', 'Like most male Orcs, Ulag possessed a muscular build with the characteristic green skin and prominent tusks of his race. His years as a bandit likely left him battle-scarred, with calloused hands and weathered features from living rough in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness.', '* Ysolda - Business partner in Sleeping Tree Sap trade, though their relationship was purely transactional * Giants of Sleeping Tree Camp - Hostile entities who ultimately caused his death * Former Stronghold - Estranged from his traditional Orcish community * Various Bandits - Likely maintained loose alliances with other criminal elements', 'Ulag operated as an independent bandit specializing in the acquisition and trade of valuable commodities, particularly Sleeping Tree Sap. His arrangement with Ysolda suggests he had evolved beyond common raiding to become something of a criminal entrepreneur.', '* Proficient in light armor combat techniques * Experienced in navigating Skyrim''s criminal networks * Skilled negotiator and trader of illegal goods * Knowledgeable about giant territories and behavior * Capable of stealth operations and smuggling', 'Likely spoke in the direct, pragmatic manner typical of Orcs, but with more sophisticated vocabulary than common bandits due to his merchant activities. Probably tempered the aggressive Orcish speech patterns when conducting business with non-Orcs.', '* Establish himself as the primary supplier of Sleeping Tree Sap in Skyrim * Accumulate enough wealth to potentially buy protection or establish his own criminal operation * Expand his trading network beyond Whiterun Hold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ulfberth_war-bear', 'Ulfberth War-Bear is a skilled Nord merchant and blacksmith who manages the successful Warmaiden''s shop in Whiterun alongside his wife Adrianne Avenicci. Though he primarily handles the business side of their operation, he possesses considerable knowledge of arms and armor, serving as a respected fixture of Whiterun''s merchant community.', 'nord, blacksmith, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Ulfberth likely received traditional Nord warrior training in his youth before focusing on merchanting and smithing. He met Adrianne Avenicci, daughter of the Whiterun Steward, and their shared passion for weaponsmithing led to both marriage and a successful business partnership running Warmaiden''s.', 'Ulfberth is a warm and gregarious businessman who takes genuine pride in the quality of his merchandise and his wife''s craftsmanship. He maintains a professional yet friendly demeanor with customers while displaying deep loyalty to both his wife and the community of Whiterun. Despite his merchant lifestyle, he retains the hardy warrior spirit typical of Nord culture.', 'A sturdy Nord man of middle age with a robust, muscular build developed through years of handling heavy weapons and armor. He has the weathered features typical of a Nord, with facial hair and strong, calloused hands from his work in the shop.', '* Adrianne Avenicci - Beloved wife and business partner who he deeply respects for her smithing skills * Proventus Avenicci - Father-in-law and Whiterun''s steward, maintaining a cordial family relationship * Whiterun Guards - Regular customers who help maintain good business relations * Local Merchants - Maintains friendly professional relationships with other Whiterun shopkeepers', 'Co-owner and primary salesman of Warmaiden''s, handling all customer interactions and business transactions while his wife focuses on crafting. He manages inventory, negotiations, and shop operations during business hours, maintaining one of Whiterun''s most successful establishments.', '* Experienced merchant with strong bargaining and customer service abilities * Knowledgeable about weapons and armor, including their quality, value, and proper use * Competent warrior skilled with two-handed weapons, particularly warhammers * Basic blacksmithing knowledge, though not as skilled as his wife', 'Speaks in a friendly, welcoming manner with a thick Nord accent, often using casual language and warrior terminology. His speech reflects both his merchant expertise and Nord heritage, frequently praising his wife''s craftsmanship while maintaining a professional sales approach.', '* Maintain and expand Warmaiden''s success as Whiterun''s premier weapons and armor shop * Support his wife''s crafting career while handling the business aspects of their partnership * Uphold his reputation as a trusted merchant in the Whiterun community * Continue providing quality arms and armor to Whiterun''s defenders');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ulfgar_the_unending', 'Ulfgar the Unending is a legendary Nord warrior from the Second Era who earned his place in the Hall of Valor through countless battles alongside Ysgramor''s Five Hundred Companions. His epithet ''the Unending'' speaks to his extraordinary endurance and unwavering dedication in combat, traits that made him a living legend among the ancient Nords.', 'nord, warrior, sovngarde, companions', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born in the late Merethic Era, Ulfgar joined Ysgramor''s campaign against the Snow Elves, proving himself as an exceptional warrior during the Return. His most notable achievements came during the prolonged campaigns across Skyrim, where he earned his nickname by reportedly fighting for days without rest. After his eventual death, his legendary status earned him a place in the Hall of Valor, where he continues to feast with his closest companions.', 'Ulfgar embodies the stoic warrior archetype, preferring to let his actions speak louder than words. His silent nature masks a deep sense of loyalty to his fellow warriors and an unshakeable commitment to Nord traditions and values. Despite his fearsome reputation in battle, he maintains a contemplative demeanor in the Hall of Valor, finding contentment in the company of his eternal companions.', 'Ulfgar is a towering Nord warrior with a muscular build shaped by centuries of combat. His weathered face bears the scars of countless battles, while his steel-gray eyes reflect the wisdom of ages. His physical presence commands respect, standing a full head taller than most other warriors in the Hall of Valor.', '* Nikulas - Fellow warrior and eternal companion in the Hall of Valor * Erlendr - Trusted shield-brother from the ancient campaigns * Hunroor - Close combat companion and drinking partner in Shor''s realm * Ysgramor - Revered leader and commander during the Return', 'As a resident of the Hall of Valor, Ulfgar serves as an eternal warrior in Shor''s army, ready to fight in the final battle of Alduin''s prophecy. In life, he was a renowned member of the Five Hundred Companions, serving as both a warrior and leader in numerous campaigns across Skyrim.', '* Master of heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Exceptional endurance and stamina in battle, leading to his nickname * Expert swordsman specializing in traditional Nord combat styles * Skilled warrior leader with extensive battlefield tactical knowledge * Proficient in ancient Nord war cries and battle songs', 'Though capable of speech, Ulfgar maintains a deliberate silence, communicating primarily through subtle gestures and knowing looks. When he does speak, his voice carries the weight of ages, using archaic Nord expressions and formal battlefield terminology.', '* Maintain eternal vigilance in preparation for the final battle of Alduin''s prophecy * Preserve the honor and traditions of the ancient Nord warriors * Guide worthy warriors who enter the Hall of Valor * Stand ready to answer Shor''s call when needed');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ulfr_the_blind', 'Ulfr the Blind is a Nord bandit who serves as an unlikely guardian of White River Watch, maintaining his post despite his complete loss of sight. His position as uncle to the bandit leader Hajvarr Iron-Hand has earned him a place of respect within the group, though his disability limits him to serving as a preliminary sentry who relies on his acute hearing and memory of visitors'' voices.', 'nord, thief, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born to a farming family in Skyrim, Ulfr lost his sight in his early adult years, possibly due to disease or injury, though the exact cause remains unknown. His nephew Hajvarr took him in when no one else would, giving him purpose as a cave guardian despite his blindness, and teaching him to use his other senses to identify friend from foe.', 'Despite his circumstances, Ulfr maintains a stoic and dutiful demeanor, taking pride in his role as guardian. He displays remarkable adaptation to his blindness, having developed keen hearing and a strong memory for voices, though his isolation has made him somewhat paranoid and quick to raise alarm at unfamiliar sounds.', 'A weathered Nord male of advanced years, with clouded, sightless eyes and a sturdy, though somewhat hunched frame from years of sitting at his post. His face bears the deep wrinkles and scars common to those who''ve lived a harsh life in Skyrim''s wilderness.', '* Hajvarr Iron-Hand - Nephew and leader of the bandit group, who provided him sanctuary * Rodulf - Fellow bandit who regularly checks on him * White River Watch Bandits - Colleagues who respect his role despite his disability * Local Farmers - Former peers from his pre-bandit life, now estranged', 'Ulfr serves as the primary sentry for White River Watch''s lower entrance, using his heightened hearing to screen visitors. His position, while seemingly simple, is crucial as he acts as the first line of defense against intruders, maintaining the illusion of reading to appear less threatening to potential threats.', '* Exceptional hearing ability developed to compensate for blindness * Strong memory for voices and vocal patterns * Basic combat training from his pre-blind days * Ability to maintain calm under pressure and effectively raise alarm', 'Ulfr speaks in a gruff, cautious manner typical of Nord bandits, but with an added edge of wariness that comes from relying solely on sound to identify others. His speech patterns are direct and questioning, always seeking to verify the identity of those who approach.', '* Maintain his usefulness to the bandit group despite his disability * Protect his nephew''s stronghold from intruders and threats * Preserve his dignity and independence despite his blindness * Continue serving as an effective sentry despite his limitations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ulfric_stormcloak', 'Ulfric Stormcloak is the charismatic and controversial Jarl of Windhelm who leads the Stormcloak Rebellion against Imperial rule in Skyrim. A former student of the Greybeards and master of the Thu''um, he became infamous for killing High King Torygg in a duel, catalyzing a civil war that would divide Skyrim between those who see him as a liberator and those who view him as a dangerous radical.', 'nord, warrior, noble, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_ulfric', '', 'Born into the noble Stormcloak clan, Ulfric trained with the Greybeards on High Hrothgar in his youth, learning the Way of the Voice. He left his studies to fight in the Great War against the Aldmeri Dominion, where he was captured and tortured by the Thalmor, an experience that deeply affected his later views. After the Empire signed the White-Gold Concordat banning Talos worship, Ulfric''s sense of betrayal led him to start a rebellion for Skyrim''s independence.', 'Ulfric is proud, charismatic, and deeply committed to what he sees as Skyrim''s best interests, though his methods are often controversial. He possesses natural leadership abilities and genuine conviction in his cause, but can be rigid in his views and sometimes puts political goals above humanitarian concerns. While capable of great inspiration and loyalty to his followers, he shows little concern for the plight of non-Nords in his city.', 'A tall, powerfully built Nord with strong Nordic features and long blonde hair. His face bears the weathered look of a warrior, with intense eyes and battle scars that speak to his military experience. His commanding physical presence matches his role as a leader and warrior.', '* Galmar Stone-Fist - His most trusted general and friend * High King Torygg - Former High King whom he killed in combat * General Tullius - His primary adversary in the Civil War * The Greybeards - His former teachers whom he left to fight in the Great War * Thalmor - Complex antagonistic relationship, though they see him as an asset to their goals * Dark Elves and Argonians - Strained relationship with these minorities in his city', 'Jarl of Windhelm and leader of the Stormcloak Rebellion. He maintains dual responsibilities of governing Eastmarch hold while commanding his revolutionary forces against the Empire. His daily routine involves holding court in the Palace of the Kings, where he manages both civil and military matters.', '* Master of the Thu''um, particularly skilled with Unrelenting Force and Disarm shouts * Accomplished military commander and strategist * Skilled warrior proficient with two-handed weapons * Natural leader with strong diplomatic and oratory abilities * Experienced in Nordic traditional combat', 'Speaks with a strong Nordic accent and uses formal, often passionate rhetoric that emphasizes traditional Nord values and independence. His speech carries natural authority and charisma, frequently incorporating references to Nordic heritage and tradition.', '* Achieve independence for Skyrim from the Empire * Restore the free worship of Talos throughout Skyrim * Preserve Nord culture and traditions against outside influence * Establish himself as the true High King of Skyrim * Drive the Imperial Legion from Skyrim''s borders');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ulundil', 'Ulundil is a uniquely optimistic Altmer ranger who operates the Windhelm Stables, standing out as one of the few High Elves to embrace Nordic culture and climate. Despite the general hostility toward his kind in Windhelm, he maintains an exceptionally cheerful disposition and runs a successful horse-trading business alongside his wife.', 'highelf, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally from the Summerset Isles, Ulundil chose to leave the typically isolationist Altmer society to explore Tamriel, eventually settling in Skyrim with his wife Arivanya. His appreciation for Nordic culture and ability to thrive in Windhelm, despite its notorious prejudice against elves, suggests a long period of adaptation and integration into Nord society, likely spanning several decades given his race''s longevity.', 'Ulundil possesses an extraordinarily positive outlook on life, maintaining his cheerful demeanor even in the face of dragon attacks and racial prejudice. He embodies a philosophical approach to life, believing in accepting what cannot be changed while focusing on living life to its fullest, and demonstrates genuine interest in others regardless of their race or background.', 'As a High Elf, Ulundil possesses the characteristic height and slender build of his race, likely standing around 6''5" to 7'' tall. His features show the typical Altmer traits of high cheekbones', 'pointed ears', 'and almond-shaped eyes', 'though his face likely bears more weathering from working outdoors than most of his kin."', '* Arivanya - Beloved wife and business partner at the stables * Local Nord Community - Generally positive but likely distant relationships due to racial tensions * Stable Customers - Friendly professional relationships with regular patrons and travelers * Candlehearth Hall Regulars - Casual acquaintances from his bi-weekly visits', '* Experienced horse trainer and stable master * Competent ranger with survival skills suited to Skyrim''s harsh climate * Basic combat abilities with an iron dagger for self-defense * Horse breeding and animal husbandry expertise * Business management and trading skills');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ulves_romoran', 'Ulves Romoran is a skilled but often frustrated Dunmer cook serving as Master Neloth''s primary chef at Tel Mithryn. Despite his gruff exterior and complaints about the constant ash contaminating his cooking, he maintains a strong dedication to his culinary duties and shows unexpected depth of character through his genuine concern for his colleagues.', 'darkelf, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledunmer', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Ulves made his way to Solstheim seeking employment and eventually secured a position as Master Neloth''s cook at Tel Mithryn. His expertise in traditional Dunmer cuisine and ability to prepare Neloth''s particular favorite, canis root tea, made him an invaluable addition to the tower''s staff, though the position has proven more demanding than he initially anticipated.', 'Ulves is a hardworking but frequently irritable individual, prone to complaints about his working conditions yet maintaining a strong sense of duty. While he can be short-tempered and gruff, particularly when stressed about meal preparation, he harbors genuine care for his colleagues as evidenced by his reaction to Varona''s death and his willingness to prepare her grave.', 'A typical Dunmer male with the characteristic ashen gray skin and red eyes of his race. His hands show the calluses and minor burns typical of a longtime cook, and his posture reflects someone who spends long hours standing over cooking fires.', '* Master Neloth - Demanding employer whom he serves with a mixture of respect and exasperation * Varona Nelas - Former colleague he had a complicated but caring relationship with, showing genuine grief at her death * Ildari Sarothril - Former romantic interest who rejected his advances in favor of pursuing magical power * Tel Mithryn Residents - Generally cordial working relationships, though strained by the stresses of his position', 'Serves as the head cook at Tel Mithryn, responsible for preparing all meals for Master Neloth and other tower residents. His primary duties include brewing Neloth''s preferred canis root tea and maintaining the kitchen despite the constant challenge of ash contamination.', '* Expert in Dunmer cuisine preparation and traditional cooking methods * Specialized knowledge in brewing canis root tea to Master Neloth''s exact specifications * Basic combat abilities with an iron war axe for self-defense * Practical knowledge of local ingredients and food preservation techniques', 'Speaks in a direct, often irritable manner with frequent complaints about ash and working conditions. His vocabulary and tone reflect his working-class background and professional frustrations.', '* Maintain the quality of his cooking despite the challenging conditions of Solstheim * Find ways to better protect food supplies from ash contamination * Secure more reliable supply lines for fresh ingredients from Raven Rock * Earn greater recognition and appreciation for his culinary efforts from Master Neloth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ulyn', 'Ulyn was an ambitious Dark Elf bandit wizard who specialized in exploring Dwemer ruins and acquiring valuable artifacts. His expertise in both magic and ancient technology made him a formidable treasure hunter, though his overconfidence ultimately led to his demise in the depths of Fahlbtharz while pursuing the legendary Visage of Mzund.', 'darkelf, mage, solstheim, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_maledunmer', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Ulyn developed an early fascination with Dwemer technology and magic, likely studying at one of the Great Houses before turning to a life of banditry. He eventually made his way to Solstheim, where he formed a partnership with the warrior Eydis to explore the island''s numerous Dwemer ruins in search of valuable artifacts.', 'Ulyn was marked by an intense curiosity about Dwemer technology and a willingness to take significant risks in pursuit of valuable artifacts. His confidence in his abilities as both a wizard and a scholar often bordered on reckless overconfidence, leading him to push deeper into dangerous ruins than prudence would dictate. Despite his bandit lifestyle, he maintained scholarly habits, keeping detailed journals of his discoveries.', 'A typical Dunmer male with ashen gray skin and angular features characteristic of his race. His years of ruins exploration had left him with a wiry, athletic build, though his hands showed the telltale calluses of both spellcasting and archaeological work.', '* Eydis - Partner in exploration and treasure hunting, trusted companion in dangerous ruins * Local Bandits - Likely maintained connections with various criminal elements for fencing artifacts * Dwemer Scholars - Probable contacts within academic circles, despite his criminal activities', 'Ulyn operated as a bandit wizard specializing in the exploration and plunder of Dwemer ruins. He combined his magical abilities with his knowledge of ancient technology to access and navigate dangerous ruins, while maintaining a scholarly approach to documenting his findings.', '* Accomplished wizard with expertise in destruction and alteration magic * Advanced knowledge of Dwemer mechanisms and technology * Skilled in archaeological exploration and artifact identification * Proficient in combat magic and basic weapons use * Experienced in disarming ancient traps and security systems', 'Speaks with the refined accent and vocabulary of an educated Dunmer, often using technical terminology when discussing Dwemer artifacts and ruins. His tone typically carries an air of scholarly authority mixed with the practical directness of a seasoned adventurer.', '* Acquire the legendary Visage of Mzund from Fahlbtharz * Build a reputation as a premier expert in Dwemer artifacts and technology * Amass a personal collection of rare Dwemer artifacts * Uncover the secrets of Dwemer engineering and magical technology');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('umana', 'Umana is a skilled Redguard warrior and explorer who joined Sulla Trebatius''s expedition to Alftand, serving as his second-in-command. Her cautious nature and moral compass eventually put her at odds with Sulla''s increasingly unstable leadership, leading to a fatal confrontation in the depths of the Dwemer ruins.', 'redguard, warrior, winterhold, dwemer', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born and raised in Hammerfell, Umana trained as a traditional Redguard warrior before seeking adventure in Skyrim. She built a reputation as a capable explorer and mercenary, eventually catching the attention of Sulla Trebatius who recruited her for his ambitious expedition to uncover Dwemer secrets in Alftand. Her journal entries reveal she witnessed the gradual descent of their expedition into chaos and death.', 'Umana is pragmatic, level-headed, and possesses a strong moral compass that guides her decisions. She shows remarkable patience in dealing with Sulla''s deteriorating mental state, but has clear boundaries when it comes to needless violence or reckless behavior. Her final confrontation with Sulla demonstrates both her commitment to survival and her reluctance to engage in unnecessary bloodshed.', 'Umana has the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of a Redguard warrior, with well-defined muscles from years of combat training. Her face bears subtle scars from previous battles, and her posture reflects her military background and combat readiness.', '* Sulla Trebatius - Former expedition leader turned adversary due to his growing paranoia * J''darr and J''zhar - Khajiit brothers who were part of their expedition team * Valie - Fellow expedition member who perished in the ruins * Endrast - Expedition member whose death she witnessed', 'Umana serves as a professional explorer and mercenary warrior, specializing in dangerous expeditions into ancient ruins. Her role in Sulla''s expedition combined her combat expertise with archaeological exploration, though the venture ultimately proved disastrous.', '* Expert in close-quarters combat with sword and shield techniques * Proficient in wearing and maintaining heavy armor * Experienced in survival skills and expedition planning * Knowledgeable about Dwemer ruins and their dangers * Capable leader and tactical strategist', 'Umana speaks directly and honestly, favoring clear communication over flowery language. Her tone carries the weight of authority and experience, though she maintains a respectful demeanor even in confrontational situations.', '* Escape from Alftand alive and warn others of its dangers * Preserve the knowledge gained from the failed expedition * Find redemption for her role in the deaths of her fellow expedition members * Return to her life as a professional explorer, though with more caution in choosing future ventures');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('umurn', 'Umurn is a dedicated Orcish blacksmith and warrior living in the stronghold of Dushnikh Yal, working alongside his mother Gharol at the forge while harboring ambitions of leadership. As one of Chief Burguk''s many sons born to a lesser-ranked forge-wife, he endures a demanding schedule split between smithing during the day and mining at night, all while preparing for the possibility of eventually challenging his brother for chiefdom.', 'orc, blacksmith, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Dushnikh Yal, Umurn learned the art of smithing from his mother Gharol, who holds the position of forge-wife to Chief Burguk. Despite being born to a lesser-ranked wife, he has embraced his role in the stronghold''s hierarchy, developing both his crafting skills and martial prowess. His upbringing has been shaped by Orcish traditions and the knowledge that he may one day need to prove himself worthy of leadership through combat.', 'Umurn is hardworking and disciplined, showing unwavering dedication to both his forge work and mining duties without complaint. He demonstrates profound respect for Orcish traditions and his mother''s teachings, while harboring a quiet ambition tempered by pragmatism. Though aware of his challenging position in the stronghold''s hierarchy, he maintains a determined and focused attitude toward improving his skills and preparing for future challenges.', 'Umurn possesses the characteristic robust build of an Orc warrior, with prominent tusks and the strong musculature developed through years of smithing and mining work. His hands are calloused from endless hours at the forge, and his skin bears the occasional burns and scars typical of a blacksmith.', '* Gharol - His mother and mentor in the art of blacksmithing, who pushes him to excellence * Chief Burguk - His father, though their relationship is distant due to his status as a lesser son * Nagrub - His brother and potential future rival for chiefdom * Other stronghold members - Maintains respectful but reserved relationships as befits his station', 'Umurn serves as both a blacksmith and miner in Dushnikh Yal, working the forge during daylight hours and spending his nights in the mine. His position as a forge-wife''s son requires him to contribute significantly to the stronghold''s resource production and weapon crafting needs.', '* Accomplished blacksmith capable of working with various metals and creating weapons * Experienced miner with knowledge of ore extraction and processing * Capable warrior trained in traditional Orcish combat techniques * Proficient with both one-handed weapons and archery', 'Umurn speaks directly and honestly, without embellishment or excessive words. His speech often focuses on practical matters and demonstrates respect for Orcish traditions and his mother''s teachings.', '* Create a weapon worthy of a chief, demonstrating his mastery of the forge * Develop the strength and skill necessary to potentially challenge for chiefdom * Earn greater respect and status within the stronghold through his craftsmanship * Uphold and honor Orcish traditions while advancing his position in the stronghold hierarchy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('una', 'Una is a diligent Nord servant at the Blue Palace in Solitude who takes her housekeeping duties with utmost seriousness despite her apparent lack of enthusiasm for the work. Behind her stern and practical exterior lies a superstitious nature, revealed by her fear of the palace''s supernatural elements, particularly the ghost in the Pelagius Wing.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Una likely came from a working-class Nord family and found employment at the Blue Palace due to her strong work ethic and attention to detail. Her years of service have made her intimately familiar with the palace''s layout and operations, though her experiences with supernatural occurrences in the Pelagius Wing have left her with a lingering wariness of the palace''s darker corners.', 'Una is a pragmatic and no-nonsense individual who values order and cleanliness above all else. She shows little patience for frivolity or inefficiency, particularly when it comes to her colleague Erdi''s work habits, and maintains a somewhat gruff exterior that masks her underlying anxieties about the supernatural elements of her workplace.', 'As a Nord woman, Una likely possesses the typical robust build and fair features common to her race. Her years of physical labor as a servant have likely given her strong, capable hands and a sturdy frame well-suited to her daily tasks.', '* Erdi - Colleague whom she views with disapproval and mild contempt * Falk Firebeard - Superior and palace steward who oversees her work * Lisette - Acquaintance from the Bards College whom she occasionally interacts with * Palace Staff - Professional relationships maintained through daily interactions', 'Una serves as a housekeeper and servant in the Blue Palace, responsible for maintaining cleanliness and order throughout the building. Her duties include cleaning, making beds, clearing spider webs from the Pelagius Wing during annual cleanings, and various other household tasks necessary for the palace''s upkeep.', '* Experienced in household maintenance and cleaning techniques * Knowledge of proper noble household etiquette and protocols * Capable of basic pest control and spider removal * Familiar with the layout and secret passages of the Blue Palace', 'Una speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner with a slight tone of irritation or exasperation. Her vocabulary is simple but proper, befitting her position as a palace servant, and she often makes curt, practical statements that reflect her no-nonsense attitude.', '* Maintain the highest standards of cleanliness and order in the Blue Palace * Avoid supernatural encounters, particularly in the Pelagius Wing * Perhaps advance to a more senior domestic position within the palace hierarchy * Minimize interactions with her less-dedicated colleague Erdi');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('unemployed_laborer', 'A destitute Nord warrior fallen on hard times, now residing at the Frostfruit Inn in Rorikstead after losing his means of employment. Driven to desperate measures, he has performed the Black Sacrament to arrange the murder of someone who has wronged him, revealing the darker depths to which unemployment has driven this once-honest laborer.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Once a hardworking manual laborer in Skyrim''s construction and farming sectors, he lost his livelihood during the civil war''s economic downturn. Having exhausted his savings and unable to find new work, he took refuge at the Frostfruit Inn, where mounting bitterness and desperation eventually led him to seek revenge through the Dark Brotherhood.', 'A formerly proud working man whose extended unemployment has left him bitter, desperate, and morally compromised. Though he maintains a facade of Nordic stoicism, his resort to murder-for-hire reveals deep-seated anger and resentment at his circumstances. Direct and businesslike in his dealings, he approaches even matters of assassination with the practical mindset of a laborer arranging services.', 'A weathered Nord male with the muscular build and calloused hands typical of someone accustomed to physical labor. His once-robust frame shows signs of recent weight loss and hardship, though he still maintains the strong physical presence characteristic of his race. His face bears the creases and weathering of someone who has spent years working outdoors.', '* Rorik - Former employer in Rorikstead, relationship now strained * Jouane Manette - Healer who occasionally provides charitable care * Mralki - Innkeeper who allows him to stay at Frostfruit Inn despite mounting tabs * Erik the Slayer - Young warrior who shows him occasional kindness', 'Currently unemployed after years of working as a general laborer in construction and farming. His desperate situation has led him to linger at the Frostfruit Inn, where he struggles to maintain his dignity while seeking new employment opportunities.', '* Experienced in physical labor and construction work * Basic proficiency with common tools and farming implements * Rudimentary combat abilities with simple weapons * Knowledge of basic carpentry and masonry * Familiar with agricultural techniques common to Skyrim', 'Speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of working-class Nords, with a slight accent common to the Whiterun Hold region. His tone carries an underlying edge of bitterness and urgency, especially when discussing the contract.', '* Secure revenge against those he believes responsible for his current situation * Find stable employment to rebuild his life and dignity * Restore his standing in the community of Rorikstead * Eventually save enough gold to establish his own homestead');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ungrien', 'Ungrien is a timid Wood Elf vendor at the Black-Briar Meadery who lives under constant fear of his employer, Maven Black-Briar. Despite his outward enthusiasm and rehearsed praise for the meadery''s products, he harbors deep anxiety about his position and possibly his life, revealing the darker side of Maven''s business empire.', 'woodelf, merchant, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally from Valenwood, Ungrien came to Skyrim seeking economic opportunities like many other Wood Elves. He eventually found himself in Riften, where his natural salesmanship caught Maven Black-Briar''s attention, leading to his current position at the meadery. His initial gratitude for the job has since transformed into fear-driven loyalty.', 'Ungrien exhibits a nervous and submissive disposition, constantly trying to please his employer through rehearsed promotional speeches and excessive praise. Beneath his practiced enthusiasm lies a deeply fearful individual who understands the precarious nature of his position, willing to reveal his true feelings only when assured of confidentiality.', 'As a Wood Elf, Ungrien possesses the characteristic lean build and pointed ears of his race, with a slightly shorter stature than the local Nords. His face often displays nervous tension, with frequent worried glances and a tendency to fidget when discussing his employer.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Feared employer who holds power over his livelihood and possibly his life * Haelga - Proprietor of the bunkhouse where he resides * Fellow Meadery Workers - Maintains cautious professional relationships * Meadery Customers - Interactions limited to rehearsed sales pitches and careful conversation', 'Ungrien serves as the primary vendor and promotional spokesperson at the Black-Briar Meadery''s tasting counter. His duties include serving mead, promoting the brand, and maintaining Maven Black-Briar''s carefully crafted public image through rehearsed endorsements.', '* Practiced salesman with rehearsed promotional abilities * Basic combat skills with a dagger for self-defense * Knowledge of mead brewing and tasting * Developed ability to maintain composure under pressure', 'Ungrien''s speech alternates between overly enthusiastic, rehearsed promotional dialogue and nervous, hesitant responses when speaking candidly. His voice often carries an underlying tone of anxiety, especially when discussing Maven or the meadery''s business practices.', '* Maintain his position at the meadery without drawing Maven''s negative attention * Survive in Riften''s dangerous political environment * Eventually save enough money to potentially escape Maven''s influence * Find a way to ensure his personal safety while maintaining his employment');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('unmid_snow-shod', 'Unmid Snow-Shod is a fiercely loyal Nord housecarl who serves as the personal protector of Jarl Laila Law-Giver in Riften. A proud son of the influential Snow-Shod clan and devoted Stormcloak supporter, he takes his duties with utmost seriousness, maintaining constant vigilance against potential threats to the Jarl''s life.', 'nord, warrior, rift, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born into the prestigious Snow-Shod family of Riften, Unmid was raised with strong Nordic values and a deep hatred for the Empire. His upbringing in a wealthy merchant family, combined with his father Vulwulf''s strong Stormcloak sympathies, shaped his political views and sense of duty. His martial prowess and unwavering loyalty earned him the coveted position of housecarl to Jarl Laila Law-Giver.', 'Unmid is stern, vigilant, and deeply suspicious of outsiders, shaped by the constant threats against his Jarl. He harbors a particular hatred for the Thieves Guild and Imperial sympathizers, showing an aggressive and uncompromising stance toward perceived enemies. Despite his hard exterior, he maintains a softer side in his romance with Anuriel, though duty always comes first.', 'A strong-built Nord warrior with the characteristic hardy physique of his race. His years of combat training and constant vigilance have kept him in peak physical condition, ready to defend his Jarl at a moment''s notice.', '* Jarl Laila Law-Giver - His sworn lord whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Anuriel - Romantic partner and the Jarl''s steward * Vulwulf Snow-Shod - Father and influential merchant * Nura Snow-Shod - Mother and temple priestess * Asgeir Snow-Shod - Brother and fellow merchant * Thieves Guild - Sworn enemies he would gladly eliminate if not for the war effort', 'As housecarl to Jarl Laila Law-Giver, Unmid serves as her personal bodyguard and last line of defense. He coordinates with the city guard to maintain security in Mistveil Keep and personally oversees all security measures to protect the Jarl.', '* Expert warrior specializing in two-handed combat with greatswords * Tactical defense and security planning expertise * Strong leadership abilities in coordinating with city guards * Advanced knowledge of combat techniques and battlefield strategy * Skilled in identifying potential threats and security risks', 'Unmid speaks in a formal, authoritative manner befitting his position, often using stern warnings and maintaining professional distance. His speech reflects both his military background and noble upbringing, though it can turn aggressive when discussing enemies of Riften or the Stormcloak cause.', '* Ensure the continued safety and security of Jarl Laila Law-Giver at all costs * Support the Stormcloak cause and see Ulfric Stormcloak crowned High King * Eliminate the Thieves Guild presence in Riften when resources allow * Maintain the honor and reputation of the Snow-Shod family name');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('uraccen', 'Uraccen is a hardened Breton prisoner and former Forsworn member serving a life sentence in Cidhna Mine, known for his pragmatic approach to survival in the harsh prison environment. As the father of an undercover Forsworn agent, he maintains a complex balance between his revolutionary ideals and his parental concerns, while serving as an unofficial guide to new inmates.', 'breton, warrior, witch, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally serving a Nord nobleman, Uraccen was forced to flee when his master was murdered, though he maintains his innocence in the crime. He subsequently joined the Forsworn movement, embracing their ancient traditions and participating in their violent campaign against Nord rule until his capture and imprisonment in Cidhna Mine.', 'Uraccen is a practical realist who has adapted to the brutal realities of prison life, offering straightforward advice to new inmates while maintaining a degree of calculated distance. Despite his hardened exterior, he harbors deep concern for his daughter Uaile and shows glimpses of vulnerability when speaking of her, while his commitment to Forsworn ideology remains undiminished by his imprisonment.', 'As a Breton, Uraccen possesses the typical shorter stature and lean build characteristic of his race. Years of mining work have left him muscular but weathered, with calloused hands and a body marked by the harsh conditions of prison life.', '* Uaile - His daughter who serves as an undercover Forsworn agent * Madanach - Prison leader and King in Rags whom he respects but has limited access to * Borkul the Beast - Views with caution as Madanach''s dangerous enforcer * Fellow Forsworn prisoners - Maintains solidarity but practical relationships * Nord nobility - Harbors deep resentment due to past experiences', 'Uraccen serves as a prisoner-miner in Cidhna Mine, forced to extract silver ore under harsh conditions. His unofficial role as an advisor to new inmates gives him a measure of influence within the prison''s social hierarchy.', '* Proficient in witchblade combat techniques combining magic and weapons * Experienced in prison survival and social navigation * Mining and basic metalwork from years of forced labor * Knowledge of Forsworn customs and guerrilla tactics * Basic alchemy and magic abilities typical of Breton heritage', 'Uraccen speaks in a direct, unembellished manner, delivering harsh truths without sugar-coating. His tone carries the weight of experience, often punctuated by bitter undertones when discussing Nord rule or prison conditions.', '* Survive his life sentence while maintaining his dignity and Forsworn principles * Protect and maintain some connection with his daughter Uaile * Support the Forsworn cause from within prison however possible * Navigate prison politics while avoiding unnecessary conflicts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('urag_gro-shub', 'Urag gro-Shub is a scholarly Orc who serves as the dedicated librarian of The Arcanaeum, the College of Winterhold''s vast repository of magical knowledge. His fierce protection of the college''s literary collection and extensive knowledge of arcane texts make him an invaluable, if intimidating, resource for scholars seeking rare magical knowledge.', 'orc, mage, scholar, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born into an Orcish stronghold, Urag defied the warrior tradition of his people to pursue academic interests, eventually finding his way to the College of Winterhold. His exceptional intellect and passionate dedication to preserving knowledge earned him the prestigious position of head librarian at The Arcanaeum, where he has served for several decades, carefully curating and protecting its vast collection.', 'Urag is stern, meticulous, and deeply protective of his books, treating them with the same reverence an Orcish warrior might show their ancestral weapons. Though initially gruff and intimidating, he shows genuine enthusiasm when engaging with serious scholars and will go to great lengths to assist those who demonstrate proper respect for knowledge and learning.', 'Despite his scholarly pursuits, Urag maintains the imposing physical presence typical of his Orcish heritage, with prominent tusks and a muscular build. His face bears the weathered look of one who has spent decades poring over ancient texts, with deep-set eyes that reflect both intelligence and intensity.', '* Savos Aren - Respected superior and fellow scholar who trusts him completely with The Arcanaeum''s operation * Tolfdir - Colleague who shares his appreciation for preservation of knowledge * College Students - Maintains a stern but ultimately helpful relationship with serious students * Book Collectors - Network of contacts across Skyrim who help acquire rare texts * Enthir - Occasional business relationship for acquiring rare books through unofficial channels', 'As the Master Librarian of The Arcanaeum, Urag oversees one of Tamriel''s most comprehensive collections of magical texts and artifacts. He manages all aspects of the library''s operation, from acquisition and preservation of materials to assisting researchers and maintaining strict standards for the handling of rare books.', '* Expert-level knowledge of magical theory and arcane literature * Skilled restoration magic practitioner, particularly in preservation spells * Master-level expertise in book preservation and restoration techniques * Proficient in multiple languages including Ancient Nordic and Dwemeris * Extensive knowledge of Tamrielic history and magical artifacts', 'Urag speaks in a direct, authoritative manner with a slight growl in his voice, often employing academic terminology. His tone can shift from threatening when warning about mishandling books to enthusiastic when discussing rare texts or interesting magical theories.', '* Maintain and expand The Arcanaeum''s collection of rare and valuable texts * Preserve ancient knowledge for future generations of mages * Document and catalog all known information about the Eye of Magnus * Establish The Arcanaeum as the premier magical library in all of Tamriel');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('urog', 'Urog is a fierce and independent Orc ranger from Narzulbur stronghold who struggles with her father''s leadership while striving to prove herself as a capable hunter and warrior. She represents the tension between traditional Orcish values and personal ambition, learning the ways of survival from her great-aunt Yatul while harboring deep suspicions about the circumstances of her mother''s death.', 'orc, warrior, hunter, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Narzulbur stronghold as the daughter of Chief Mauhulakh, Urog grew up under the shadow of her mother''s mysterious death and her father''s perceived weakness as a leader. She was mentored from a young age by her great-aunt Yatul, who taught her hunting and survival skills, helping shape her into a capable ranger away from her father''s influence.', 'Urog is strong-willed, confrontational, and often abrasive, particularly toward her father whom she views as weak and undeserving of his position. Despite her harsh exterior, she shows deep loyalty to her tribe and genuine respect for her great-aunt Yatul''s teachings. She carries emotional wounds regarding her mother''s death and struggles with balancing tribal loyalty against her personal doubts about leadership.', 'As an Orc female, Urog possesses the characteristic robust build and strong features of her race, with prominent tusks and muscular frame developed through constant training and hunting. Her body bears the scars and calluses of someone who spends considerable time in the wilderness tracking prey.', '* Mauhulakh (Father) - Strained relationship marked by distrust and resentment * Yatul (Great-aunt) - Respected mentor and primary teacher in hunting skills * Dushnamub (Brother) - Dismissive of his attempts to explain family dynamics * Bolar (Great-aunt) - Secondary family elder in the stronghold * Mother (Deceased) - Harbors suspicions about the circumstances of her death', 'Urog serves as a hunter and provider for the Narzulbur stronghold, working alongside her great-aunt Yatul to ensure the tribe''s survival through hunting and gathering. She also maintains warrior training, practicing with axes daily to uphold Orcish martial traditions.', '* Expert tracker and hunter, particularly skilled in tracking wildlife in snowy conditions * Proficient axe fighter with daily training routine * Wilderness survival specialist with extensive knowledge of Eastmarch''s terrain * Capable of providing food and resources for the stronghold through hunting', 'Urog speaks directly and often confrontationally, with little patience for pleasantries or excuses. Her speech reflects both her Orcish heritage and her independent nature, frequently containing challenging or accusatory undertones, especially when addressing her father.', '* Uncover the truth about her mother''s death and her father''s possible involvement * Prove herself as a capable hunter and warrior worthy of respect in the stronghold * Eventually challenge the current leadership structure of Narzulbur * Maintain the stronghold''s prosperity through her hunting abilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('urzoga_gra-shugurz', 'Urzoga gra-Shugurz is a formidable Orcish warrior who serves as the iron-fisted overseer of Cidhna Mine, Markarth''s notorious prison-mine complex. Her unwavering dedication to maintaining order and discipline has earned her a fearsome reputation among both prisoners and fellow guards, while her position of authority reflects the rare achievement of an Orc woman rising to power within the Nord-dominated Reach.', 'orc, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born into the Shugurz clan, Urzoga grew up learning the warrior traditions of the Orsimer while developing a strict sense of discipline and hierarchy. Her path diverged from the typical Orc stronghold life when she and her brother Mulush sought opportunities in Markarth, where her commanding presence and unwavering loyalty caught the attention of the Silver-Blood family. Years of proven service in their employ eventually earned her the position of prison overseer.', 'Urzoga embodies the archetypal Orcish values of strength and honor, but channels them through a lens of rigid authority rather than traditional tribal warfare. She maintains an intimidating demeanor that brooks no argument or resistance, viewing any challenge to her authority as a personal affront that must be immediately crushed. Despite her harsh exterior, she holds a deep sense of duty and takes pride in maintaining order within the prison system.', 'Urzoga possesses the powerful build typical of Orsimer warriors, with well-developed muscles earned through years of combat training and guard duty. Her green-skinned face bears the characteristic tusks of her race, along with several battle scars that add to her intimidating presence. She stands slightly taller than the average Orc female, using her imposing stature to full effect when asserting authority.', '* Mulush gro-Shugurz - Brother and fellow Silver-Blood employee who operates the smelter * Silver-Blood Family - Employers who trust her to maintain order in their prison-mine * Prison Guards - Subordinates who both respect and fear her authority * Prisoners - Maintains strictly professional and intimidating relationship with inmates * Markarth Guard - Professional working relationship, though keeps distance from regular city guards', 'As overseer of Cidhna Mine, Urzoga manages both the security operations and forced labor aspects of Markarth''s prison system. She coordinates guard rotations, oversees prisoner work assignments, and ensures a steady flow of silver ore production for the Silver-Blood family. Her position requires her to balance the demands of prison security with maintaining productive mining operations.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat and close-quarters prisoner control techniques * Skilled in intimidation and crowd control methods * Proficient in prison security protocols and escape prevention * Advanced knowledge of mining operations and prisoner management * Capable warrior with traditional Orcish weapon training', 'Urzoga speaks in short, commanding sentences with a deep, gravelly voice typical of Orsimer, frequently employing threats and intimidation tactics. Her vocabulary is direct and unembellished, focusing on maintaining authority through verbal dominance rather than excessive explanation.', '* Maintain absolute control over Cidhna Mine''s prisoner population * Advance her position within the Silver-Blood organization * Prove that an Orc woman can be more effective at maintaining order than any Nord guard * Ensure the continued profitability of the mine''s operation * Uphold her family''s reputation in Markarth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('usha', 'Usha was a troubled Argonian miner and skooma addict who met a tragic end in solitude near Ashfallow Citadel. Despite his struggles with addiction, he maintained a romantic relationship and accumulated modest wealth through his mining work, suggesting a complex character caught between success and personal demons.', 'argonian, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally drawn to Solstheim for its mining opportunities, Usha likely worked various mining operations across the island, eventually establishing himself near Ashfallow Citadel. His initial success as a miner was gradually overshadowed by a developing skooma addiction, which ultimately led to his isolation in a remote wooden structure where he spent his final days.', 'Usha exhibited traits of a functioning addict - capable of maintaining work relationships and romantic connections while struggling with his dependency. His choice of an isolated dwelling suggests a reclusive nature, possibly driven by shame or a desire to hide his addiction. Despite his struggles, the presence of valuable items and a lover''s letter indicates he maintained some level of responsibility and emotional connections.', 'A mature Argonian male with weathered scales showing signs of hard labor and the physical toll of skooma addiction. His robust frame, developed through years of mining work, would have been somewhat diminished in his final days due to his substance abuse.', '* Unknown Lover - Author of the letter found near his body, suggesting a significant romantic relationship * East Empire Company - Likely professional connection due to the presence of their strongbox * Local Miners - Probable working relationships from his mining activities * Skooma Dealers - Regular contacts who supplied his addiction', 'Usha worked primarily as a miner, focusing on gold ore extraction in the Solstheim region. His connection to the East Empire Company suggests he may have held official mining rights or contracts with the organization.', '* Experienced miner with knowledge of ore extraction and prospecting * Proficient in identifying valuable mineral deposits * Physical strength and endurance from years of mining work * Basic lockpicking abilities, as suggested by his possession of a strongbox', 'Given his Argonian heritage and likely years spent in Morrowind/Solstheim, Usha likely spoke with the characteristic Argonian accent and syntax, potentially using traditional Argonian expressions. His speech patterns would have become increasingly erratic in his final days due to skooma use.', '* Maintain enough mining productivity to support his skooma habit * Keep his addiction hidden from his lover and professional contacts * Accumulate wealth through mining operations * Eventually overcome his skooma addiction, though ultimately unsuccessful');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('uthgerd_the_unbroken', 'Uthgerd the Unbroken is a formidable Nord warrior whose failed attempt to join the Companions left her with a fierce desire to prove her worth. Despite her intimidating presence at the Bannered Mare, she carries the weight of a past tragedy that drives her to seek redemption through honorable combat.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Originally attempting to join the Companions in her younger years, Uthgerd accidentally killed a young initiate during her trial, resulting in her rejection from the warrior guild. This incident haunts her conscience but strengthened her resolve to prove herself worthy through legitimate combat. She settled in Whiterun, building a reputation as a capable warrior while carrying the burden of her past mistake.', 'Uthgerd is a proud and stubborn warrior who masks her inner turmoil with a gruff, challenging demeanor. She values honor in combat and despises cheap tactics or manipulation, preferring straightforward confrontation. Despite her tough exterior, she harbors deep regret over her past actions and seeks to redeem herself through honorable conduct.', 'A tall, muscular Nord woman with weathered features and battle scars that speak to her warrior lifestyle. Her face bears the hardened look of someone who has seen considerable combat, with distinctive war paint accentuating her fierce countenance. Her powerful physique reflects years of martial training and regular combat practice.', '* The Companions - Strained relationship due to her failed initiation and the death of a young initiate * Hulda - Professional acquaintance as regular patron of the Bannered Mare * Mikael the Bard - Frequent antagonist at the Bannered Mare, whom she barely tolerates * Local Mercenaries - Respected peer among Whiterun''s warrior community', 'Uthgerd works as a freelance warrior-for-hire, taking on contracts that allow her to prove her combat prowess. She spends much of her time at the Bannered Mare, where she often challenges others to prove their worth in hand-to-hand combat.', '* Expert in heavy armor combat and two-handed weapons * Skilled in hand-to-hand combat and brawling * Proficient in Nordic combat techniques and battlefield tactics * Exceptional physical strength and endurance from years of training', 'Uthgerd speaks in a direct, confrontational manner with a thick Nordic accent, often challenging others to prove themselves. Her speech is peppered with warrior terminology and references to combat, reflecting her militant lifestyle.', '* Prove her worth as a warrior and redeem herself from past mistakes * Find worthy opponents who can match her in honorable combat * Eventually earn the respect of the Companions, even if never joining their ranks * Build a legacy as a renowned warrior of Whiterun');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vagrant', 'A desperate survivor dwelling in Riften''s infamous Ratway Vaults, this vagrant represents the darker side of Skyrim''s harsh society. Once a productive member of society, they have descended into a territorial and aggressive existence in the underground tunnels, attacking intruders to protect their meager possessions and claimed territory.', 'nord, thief, rift', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a common laborer or farmer who lost everything during the civil war or economic hardships, they were forced into Riften''s underground warren of tunnels and sewers. Years of surviving in the harsh conditions of The Ratway have stripped away their former identity and civilization, leaving them as one of many territorial drifters who claim small sections of the vaults as their own.', 'Highly territorial and aggressive, showing clear signs of mental deterioration from prolonged isolation and harsh living conditions. Demonstrates extreme paranoia and hostility toward outsiders, attacking anyone who enters their claimed space without hesitation or negotiation. Their behavior suggests a complete breakdown of social norms and trust in others.', 'Weather-beaten and gaunt from years of poor nutrition and underground living, with unkempt hair and beard showing signs of self-neglect. Their body bears numerous scars from fights and accidents in the Ratway, while their skin has become pale from minimal exposure to sunlight. Their eyes hold a wild, desperate look common to those who have lived too long in darkness.', '* Fellow Vagrants - Maintains uneasy territorial boundaries with other Ratway dwellers * Lowlife Skeever - A mangy skeever that shares their territory and serves as both pest and occasional food source * Riften Guards - Viewed as threats who occasionally attempt to clear out the Ratway * Thieves Guild - Tolerated presence in the Ratway, though kept at a distance', 'Territorial scavenger who survives by claiming and defending a small section of the Ratway Vaults. Their days are spent gathering food, maintaining their shelter, and defending their space from intruders or other vagrants who might try to claim it.', '* Proficient in close-quarters combat with daggers and improvised weapons * Experienced archer capable of defending territory from range * Skilled at urban foraging and survival in underground environments * Adept at lockpicking and scavenging valuable items', 'Speaks in short, aggressive bursts with a hoarse voice from limited social interaction. Their vocabulary is simple and direct, often consisting of threats and territorial warnings delivered in a hostile tone.', '* Defend their claimed territory in the Ratway Vaults at all costs * Survive another day in the harsh underground environment * Acquire enough resources to maintain their isolated existence * Avoid being expelled from the Ratway by authorities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vahlok_the_jailor', 'Vahlok the Jailor was a legendary Dragon Priest who earned his title after defeating and imprisoning the traitor Miraak in ancient times. Known for his unwavering loyalty to the dragons and exceptional magical abilities, he served as both ruler of Solstheim and eternal warden of Miraak until his death.', 'nord, mage, solstheim, dragon', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Rising through the ranks of Dragon Priests during the Merethic Era, Vahlok distinguished himself through his steadfast devotion to the Dragon Cult. When Miraak''s betrayal was discovered, Vahlok engaged him in an epic battle that lasted for days and reportedly separated Solstheim from mainland Skyrim. After emerging victorious, he was appointed ruler of Solstheim and tasked with ensuring Miraak would never escape.', 'Vahlok exemplifies absolute loyalty and dedication to duty, traits that earned him the dragons'' complete trust. He is methodical and vigilant, with an unwavering sense of justice that drives him to punish those who betray their oaths. Even in death, his spirit maintains its steadfast nature, continuing to guard against potential threats.', 'As a Dragon Priest, Vahlok possessed a tall, imposing figure befitting his authoritative position. His physical form has long since deteriorated to a preserved skeletal state, though his presence remains intimidating. His ethereal essence radiates ancient power and authority.', '* Dragons - Absolutely loyal servant and trusted enforcer * Miraak - Sworn enemy and prisoner whom he was tasked to guard * Dragon Cult - Respected leader and exemplar of loyalty * People of Solstheim - Former subjects under his rule as Dragon Priest', 'Vahlok served as both the ruler of Solstheim and the designated jailor of Miraak. His primary duty was maintaining eternal vigilance over the imprisoned traitor priest, while simultaneously governing the island and maintaining order among its inhabitants.', '* Master of Dragon Priest magic with particular expertise in binding and containment spells * Powerful warrior capable of engaging in extended magical combat * Advanced knowledge of Thu''um and dragon lore * Expert in leadership and governance of territories * Specialized abilities in detecting and countering treachery', 'Vahlok speaks with the formal, archaic patterns common to Dragon Priests, favoring authoritative declarations and solemn pronouncements. His voice carries the weight of ancient power and command, often incorporating dragon language phrases into his speech.', '* Maintain eternal vigilance over Miraak''s imprisonment, even in death * Preserve the authority and honor of the Dragon Cult * Protect Solstheim from those who would threaten its established order * Punish any who would follow in Miraak''s treasonous footsteps');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vald', 'Vald is a disgraced Nord bandit turned reluctant guard who finds himself trapped between his debt to Maven Black-Briar and his forced loyalty to Mercer Frey. Once a capable thief and transporter for the Black-Briars, his catastrophic failure with the Quill of Gemination led to his current position as a surly, bitter watchdog of Riftweald Manor.', 'nord, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally operating as a freelance bandit and thief in the Rift, Vald gained enough reputation to be hired for special jobs by Maven Black-Briar. During a crucial transport mission across Lake Honrich with the valuable Quill of Gemination, he crashed his boat and lost the artifact, incurring a massive debt to Maven. To maintain some control over him, Maven arranged for him to work as Mercer Frey''s guard at Riftweald Manor, effectively trapping him in a position of servitude.', 'Vald is an aggressive, bitter individual who masks his shame and frustration behind a wall of hostility and crude behavior. His fall from relative independence to forced servitude has left him resentful and defensive, though beneath his harsh exterior lies a man desperate to escape his circumstances. He shows little loyalty to anyone except through coercion, suggesting a self-serving nature that''s been twisted by his circumstances.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the weathered features typical of someone who''s spent considerable time as a bandit and guard. His years of physical labor and combat have left him muscular and imposing, though signs of stress and poor sleep likely mark his face.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Creditor who holds his substantial debt and effectively owns his service * Mercer Frey - Current employer and master of Riftweald Manor * Vex - Former lover who now holds him in contempt * Thieves Guild - Former associates who generally look down on him * Brynjolf - Views him as nothing more than Mercer''s ''trained watchdog''', 'Vald serves as the primary guard of Riftweald Manor, Mercer Frey''s property in Riften. His position is less employment and more indentured servitude, forced upon him as a way to repay his debt to Maven Black-Briar while serving Mercer Frey''s interests.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with both daggers and swords * Experienced in guard duty and surveillance * Former boat handling skills, though his reputation is tarnished by one significant failure * Basic thieving abilities from his previous criminal career * Survival skills developed during his bandit years', 'Vald speaks in a gruff, aggressive manner with frequent use of crude language and hostile dismissals. His speech patterns reflect both his Nord heritage and his bitter disposition, often using direct threats and harsh commands to drive others away.', '* Find a way to clear his debt to Maven Black-Briar and regain his freedom * Maintain his position at Riftweald Manor to avoid worse consequences * Survive in Riften''s complex web of criminal politics without further damaging his standing');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('valdar', 'Valdar is an ancient Nord ghost who serves as the eternal guardian of Valthume, tasked with preventing the resurrection of the evil Dragon Priest Hevnoraak. A once-mighty warrior turned spectral sentinel, he maintains his vigil even as his powers fade, seeking aid from worthy adventurers to ensure his sacred duty is fulfilled.', 'nord, mage, reach', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'In life, Valdar was likely a high-ranking Nord warrior or priest who witnessed firsthand the cruelty and dark magic of Dragon Priest Hevnoraak. He dedicated himself to preventing Hevnoraak''s planned resurrection, continuing this duty even after death. His transformation into a ghost appears to be a willing sacrifice, choosing to remain bound to Valthume to maintain his eternal watch over the tomb.', 'Valdar is solemn, dutiful, and unwavering in his commitment to his sacred task. Despite his fading strength, he maintains a dignified and formal demeanor befitting his ancient status. He shows wisdom in recognizing when to seek help and gratitude toward those who aid his cause, while never losing sight of the gravity of his mission.', 'As a ghost, Valdar appears as a translucent, ethereal figure with the bearing of a proud Nord warrior. His spectral form maintains the impressive stature and muscular build he possessed in life, with strong Nordic features and an authoritative presence that commands respect even in death.', '* Hevnoraak - Sworn enemy whose resurrection he must prevent at all costs * Ancient Nord Warriors - Former brothers-in-arms who now serve as Draugr in Valthume * The Last Dragonborn - Potential ally in his mission to stop Hevnoraak * Tomb Guardians - Commands respect from the other spiritual guardians of Valthume', 'Valdar serves as the primary guardian of Valthume, specifically tasked with preventing Hevnoraak''s return to power. His role combines aspects of both warrior and mystic, using his spectral powers and ancient knowledge to maintain the magical seals that keep Hevnoraak''s power contained.', '* Mastery over spiritual energies allowing him to maintain his ghostly form * Ancient Nordic combat techniques and warrior training from his mortal life * Extensive knowledge of Dragon Priest lore and containment magic * Ability to sense and suppress Hevnoraak''s growing power * Understanding of ancient Nordic burial rites and tomb guardian protocols', 'Valdar speaks in a formal, archaic manner reflecting his ancient Nordic origins, often using grave and portentous tones when discussing the evil he guards against. His speech carries the weight of centuries and commands authority while maintaining a respectful tone toward those who would aid him.', '* Prevent Hevnoraak''s resurrection at any cost * Maintain the magical seals containing Hevnoraak''s power until a permanent solution can be found * Guide worthy champions to help complete his mission before his strength fails entirely * Ensure the evil within Valthume never threatens Skyrim again');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('valdimar', 'Valdimar is a unique Nord sorcerer who serves as housecarl in Hjaalmarch, combining traditional Nordic martial prowess with sophisticated magical abilities. Unlike most Nord warriors who distrust magic, he has embraced the arcane arts while maintaining his cultural identity as a proud son of Skyrim.', 'nord, mage, hjaalmarch, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Morthal, Valdimar studied magic under the guidance of Court Wizard Falion, breaking from the typical Nordic warrior tradition. His dedication to both martial and magical arts caught the attention of Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone, who appointed him as a guard captain before elevating him to the position of housecarl for worthy Thanes. His unusual combination of skills reflects the mysterious and magical nature of Morthal itself.', 'Valdimar is contemplative and pragmatic, showing none of the typical Nordic prejudice against magic users. He maintains a stoic demeanor and strong sense of duty characteristic of Nord warriors, while embracing intellectual pursuits and magical studies. His quiet nature masks a sharp tactical mind that effectively combines spell and steel in combat.', 'Valdimar is a tall, sturdy Nord with weather-worn features typical of Hjaalmarch''s harsh climate. His face bears the subtle marks of both warrior training and scholarly pursuit, with calculating eyes and a strong, squared jaw. His physique reflects his dual nature - muscular enough for combat but with the measured movements of a practiced mage.', '* Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone - Respected leader and patron who recognized his unique abilities * Falion - Former mentor in the magical arts and fellow magic user in Morthal * Aslfur - Professional relationship with the Jarl''s husband and steward * Morthal Guards - Commands respect from local guards due to his position and unique capabilities * Benor - Friendly rival in martial combat training', 'As housecarl to the Thane of Hjaalmarch, Valdimar serves as both protector and advisor. His duties include defending his Thane''s life and property, maintaining their holdings, and providing counsel on both martial and magical matters. His unique skill set makes him particularly valuable in the swamp-ridden, supernatural environment of Hjaalmarch.', '* Proficient in both Destruction and Restoration magic, specializing in ice spells and healing * Skilled in light and heavy armor combat techniques * Expert in defensive magic, particularly flesh spells and magical wards * Capable warrior with one-handed weapons, particularly maces * Knowledge of local lore and supernatural phenomena common to Hjaalmarch', 'Valdimar speaks with the measured tone of a well-educated Nord, choosing his words carefully and precisely. His vocabulary reflects both his martial background and magical education, seamlessly blending warrior terminology with arcane knowledge.', '* Protect and serve his Thane with unwavering loyalty and dedication * Further develop his unique combination of martial and magical abilities * Defend Hjaalmarch from both mundane and supernatural threats * Prove that magic and Nordic tradition can coexist harmoniously');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('valdr', 'Valdr is a seasoned Nord bear hunter and respected leader of a hunting band operating out of Falkreath. Known for his expertise in tracking dangerous prey and leadership capabilities, he faces personal tragedy when his hunting party falls victim to deadly spriggans in Moss Mother Cavern.', 'nord, hunter, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Falkreath Hold, Valdr learned the art of hunting from an early age, eventually becoming one of the region''s most accomplished bear hunters. He built his reputation over years of successful hunts, gathering a loyal group of fellow hunters including his close friends Niels and Ari, before their tragic demise at Moss Mother Cavern.', 'Valdr is a straightforward and pragmatic individual who values honor, loyalty, and competence above all else. Despite his gruff exterior, he shows deep concern for his men and takes personal responsibility for their welfare. The loss of his hunting companions has left him with a sense of survivor''s guilt, though he maintains his resilient Nordic spirit.', 'A weathered Nord of middle age with the robust build typical of his race, bearing numerous scars from years of dangerous hunts. His face shows the marks of someone who has spent most of his life in the wilderness, with deep-set eyes that retain a keen hunter''s awareness.', '* Niels - Deceased hunting companion and trusted friend * Ari - Fallen comrade and valued team member * Valga Vinicia - Professional acquaintance at Dead Man''s Drink * Local Falkreath hunters - Respected peer and informal leader within the hunting community', 'Valdr serves as the leader of a prominent hunting band based in Falkreath, specializing in tracking and hunting bears for their valuable pelts. After the loss of his companions, he continues his trade independently while maintaining a presence at Dead Man''s Drink.', '* Expert tracker with particular expertise in hunting bears and other dangerous game * Proficient archer capable of taking down large prey at considerable distances * Skilled wilderness survivor with extensive knowledge of Falkreath''s forests * Competent swordsman able to defend against both beasts and bandits * Natural leadership abilities honed through years of coordinating hunting parties', 'Valdr speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nordic hunters, using plain language and occasional hunting terminology. His tone carries the weight of experience and command, though tempered by recent tragedy.', '* Honor the memory of his fallen companions by maintaining their hunting traditions * Warn other hunters about the dangers of spriggans and other supernatural threats * Continue providing valuable pelts and game to Falkreath''s community * Perhaps one day rebuild his hunting band with worthy companions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('valerica', 'Valerica is an ancient and powerful vampire noble, wife to Lord Harkon and mother to Serana, who sacrificed everything to prevent her husband from fulfilling the Tyranny of the Sun prophecy. Trapped for centuries in the Soul Cairn, she is a master alchemist and necromancer who chose to protect both her daughter and the world from her husband''s megalomaniacal ambitions.', 'nord, mage, soulcairn, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_valerica', '', 'Originally a devout follower of Molag Bal, Valerica underwent the ritual to become a Daughter of Coldharbour alongside her daughter Serana. As the wife of Lord Harkon, she lived for centuries in Castle Volkihar until discovering her husband''s plans to use their daughter''s blood for the Tyranny of the Sun prophecy. She fled with two Elder Scrolls and sealed herself in the Soul Cairn to protect both the scrolls and Serana.', 'Valerica is proud, intelligent, and deeply protective of her daughter, though her methods of showing this care have been questionable. She exhibits a paranoid and distrustful nature toward outsiders, shaped by centuries of isolation and betrayal. Despite her cold exterior, she shows genuine remorse for her past mistakes and can form new alliances when convinced of others'' genuine intentions.', 'A tall, regal Nord woman with the pale complexion and glowing eyes characteristic of ancient vampires. Her features are sharp and aristocratic, bearing the eternal youth granted by vampirism while still conveying centuries of wisdom and experience. Her face shows a strong resemblance to her daughter Serana.', '* Serana - Daughter, complex relationship marked by both deep love and past mistakes * Lord Harkon - Estranged husband and bitter enemy * Dragonborn - Initially distrustful but potentially becomes an ally * Vampire Court of Castle Volkihar - Former peers, now largely hostile due to her betrayal * Ideal Masters - Entities of the Soul Cairn who imprisoned her', 'Valerica serves as a guardian of ancient knowledge and keeper of the Elder Scroll, though this is more circumstance than choice. She is a master alchemist who maintains a garden of rare ingredients, and continues her research even while trapped in the Soul Cairn.', '* Master-level knowledge of alchemy and cultivation of rare ingredients * Powerful necromantic abilities and understanding of soul magic * Expertise in vampire lore and ancient prophecies * Accomplished researcher and scholar of Elder Scrolls * Proficient in combat magic and vampire abilities', 'Valerica speaks in a formal, aristocratic manner befitting her noble status, often using archaic phrases and sophisticated vocabulary. Her tone is typically stern and suspicious, though it can soften when speaking with Serana.', '* Prevent Lord Harkon from completing the Tyranny of the Sun prophecy * Protect Serana from being sacrificed for the prophecy * Preserve the natural order and prevent vampire extinction * Rebuild her relationship with Serana * Continue her alchemical research and studies');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('valga_vinicia', 'Valga Vinicia is a resilient Imperial innkeeper who fled the Great War in Cyrodiil to establish herself in Falkreath, where she now runs the Dead Man''s Drink. Despite the somber nature of the town known for its graveyard, she maintains a cheerful disposition while serving as an important information hub for local gossip and news.', 'imperial, innkeeper, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Valga escaped the devastation of the Great War, likely leaving behind family and property to forge a new life in Skyrim. She chose Falkreath as her new home, purchasing and maintaining the Dead Man''s Drink inn, where she has become deeply integrated into the local community despite being an outsider.', 'Valga is a friendly and sociable individual who takes genuine interest in her patrons'' lives and the happenings around Falkreath. She demonstrates remarkable endurance and work ethic, managing her inn without rest, suggesting either intense dedication or perhaps trauma-induced sleeplessness from her war experiences. Though cheerful on the surface, she carries the weight of her past experiences with the war, occasionally revealing a more serious side when discussing conflicts.', 'A middle-aged Imperial woman with the characteristic olive complexion and dark features common to her race. She bears the sturdy build of someone who spends long hours on their feet, with hands toughened by years of inn work.', '* Narri - Valued employee and confidante at the Dead Man''s Drink * Tekla - Friend and occasional visitor she shows concern for * Solaf - Regular patron and source of local news * Zaria - Fellow business owner in Falkreath with whom she discusses the war * Dengeir - Former Jarl whose treatment of Tekla concerns her', 'Valga is the owner and proprietor of the Dead Man''s Drink, Falkreath''s primary inn and tavern. She manages all aspects of the business, from serving drinks and providing rooms to maintaining supplies and handling finances, making her establishment a crucial hub for both travelers and locals.', '* Expert-level bartering and business management abilities * Exceptional stamina and endurance to maintain constant operation of the inn * Strong interpersonal skills and information gathering * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Skilled cook and drink mixer', 'Valga speaks in a friendly, direct manner typical of Imperial merchants, mixing casual conversation with business acumen. Her speech often includes references to local happenings and weather, showing her connection to the community.', '* Maintain a successful business in Falkreath despite the town''s somber reputation * Create a welcoming haven for both locals and travelers * Keep informed about local and regional events to protect her new life * Eventually hire additional help to expand the inn''s services');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('valie', 'Valie was a skilled High Elf mage and thief who operated independently from formal magical institutions, known for taking on dangerous jobs for the right price. Her expertise and willingness to work outside official channels led to her recruitment for Sulla Trebatius'' ill-fated expedition into the Dwemer ruins of Alftand, where she ultimately met a tragic end at the hands of the Falmer.', 'highelf, mage, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in the Summerset Isles, Valie chose to break from the traditional path of most Altmer mages by refusing to join any formal magical institution. She made her way to Skyrim, establishing herself as a freelance mage-for-hire while developing connections in less reputable circles. Her reputation for discretion and magical prowess, combined with her willingness to work outside official channels, made her an attractive hire for dangerous expeditions.', 'Independent and self-reliant, Valie preferred to operate outside the constraints of established magical organizations. She was pragmatic and profit-motivated, willing to take calculated risks for suitable compensation. Her confidence in her abilities sometimes bordered on arrogance, a common trait among High Elves, though she backed it up with genuine skill.', 'Valie possessed the typical tall, slender build characteristic of High Elves, with the distinctive golden skin tone of her race. Her features were sharp and angular, bearing the natural elegance common to Altmer, though years of working in less than reputable circumstances had left subtle signs of wear on her otherwise ageless appearance.', '* Sulla Trebatius - Employer who hired her for the Alftand expedition * J''zhar and J''darr - Fellow expedition members who initially suspected J''darr of causing her disappearance * College of Winterhold - Deliberately maintained distance from the institution * Criminal Contacts - Various connections in Skyrim''s underground who provided job opportunities', 'Valie worked as a freelance mage and thief, taking on various jobs that required magical expertise while operating outside official channels. Her final position was as the magical expert in Sulla Trebatius'' expedition team, hired specifically for her combination of magical skill and discretion.', '* Accomplished practitioner of destruction and alteration magic * Expert in magical theory and ancient Nordic ruins * Proficient in stealth and theft * Skilled at magical artifact identification and analysis * Experience in dungeon exploration and survival', 'Valie spoke with the refined accent and vocabulary typical of educated Altmer, though she could adjust her manner of speaking to suit her audience when necessary. Her tone was often confident and slightly condescending, reflecting both her High Elven heritage and her faith in her own abilities.', '* Build wealth and reputation as an independent magical operative * Uncover valuable artifacts and magical knowledge from ancient ruins * Maintain independence from formal magical institutions while expanding her power and influence * Prove that operating outside traditional magical structures can lead to greater discoveries');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('valindor', 'Valindor is a skilled Wood Elf craftsman turned fishery worker who left behind a promising career as an armorer in Valenwood to explore Tamriel. Despite finding himself somewhat trapped in Riften''s dreary atmosphere, he maintains a gentle and philosophical outlook while carrying the refined skills of his former trade and cultural heritage.', 'woodelf, fisher, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised among the towering trees of Valenwood, Valindor spent his youth climbing and playing in the canopy with other Bosmer children. He later apprenticed under a master armorer in Silvenar, becoming highly skilled in the craft, but declined to take over the business upon his master''s death, choosing instead to explore Tamriel. His wanderings eventually led him to Riften, where he has somewhat reluctantly settled.', 'Valindor is a contemplative and kind-hearted individual who often reflects on his life choices and maintains a strong connection to his homeland''s natural beauty. Despite possible regrets about leaving Valenwood, he approaches his work with dedication and finds peace in simple labor. He shows genuine concern for others'' well-being and maintains a humble, helpful disposition despite his skilled background.', 'As a Bosmer, Valindor has the characteristic smaller stature and lithe build of his race, with the typical pointed ears and angular features of mer-folk. His years of physical labor, both as an armorer and fishery worker, have given him well-developed arm and shoulder muscles despite his lean frame.', '* Wujeeta - Shows concern for her well-being and health * Svana Far-Shield - Demonstrates friendly concern for her situation * Former Master Armorer - Deceased mentor who wished him to inherit the business * Riften Fishery Workers - Daily working relationships with fellow employees', 'Valindor works as a laborer at Riften Fishery, maintaining a strict daily schedule that includes both indoor work and time on the fishing boats. Prior to this, he was a skilled armorer''s apprentice in Silvenar, trained in sophisticated metalworking techniques.', '* Trained armorer with knowledge of advanced metalworking techniques * Experienced in physical labor and fishing boat operations * Skilled climber from his youth in Valenwood''s trees * Basic combat proficiency with daggers * Natural affinity for working with both metal and wood due to his background', 'Valindor speaks with a gentle, thoughtful tone, often expressing himself through nature-based metaphors and references to his homeland. His speech patterns reveal both his refined craftsman''s background and his current humble station.', '* Find purpose and meaning in his current life in Riften * Potentially return to his armorer roots in a meaningful way * Maintain connections to his Bosmeri heritage while adapting to his new life * Help others in his community when possible');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vals_veran', 'Vals Veran is a determined Dark Elf necromancer who has taken residence in Hillgrund''s Tomb, pursuing his controversial research into reanimating the dead. He represents the pragmatic and amoral approach to necromancy common among some Dunmer practitioners, believing that the dead should serve as tools for the advancement of the living rather than rest in peace.', 'darkelf, mage, pale', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born and raised in Morrowind, Vals Veran likely studied necromancy either secretly or in one of the Great Houses that tolerated such practices. After fleeing the devastation of Red Mountain, he wandered Skyrim seeking ancient Nordic burial sites to continue his research, eventually settling in Hillgrund''s Tomb for its rich potential in undead specimens.', 'Vals Veran is coldly intellectual and utterly convinced of the righteousness of his work, displaying the typical Dunmer traits of pride and pragmatism taken to an extreme. He shows complete disdain for Nordic burial traditions and believes that sentiment about the dead is foolish superstition that impedes practical use of available resources.', 'A typical Dunmer male with ashen gray skin and sharp, angular features characteristic of his race. His red eyes glow with particular intensity from years of necromantic practice, and his thin frame bears the slight stoop common to devoted scholars.', '* Golldir - Primary antagonist who attempts to stop his necromantic activities * Aunt Agna - Another opponent of his work in Hillgrund''s Tomb * Hillgrund''s Family - Views them as foolish traditionalists and potential research subjects * Local Nords - Generally hostile due to his defilation of their ancestral tombs', 'Necromancer and magical researcher operating independently in Skyrim''s ancient tombs. He sustains himself by scavenging valuable artifacts while pursuing his necromantic studies, showing no regard for local customs or laws regarding the dead.', '* Expert-level Necromancy and reanimation magic * Considerable knowledge of Nordic burial practices and tomb layouts * Proficient in Destruction magic for self-defense * Advanced understanding of anatomy and preservation techniques * Skilled in identifying and collecting valuable artifacts', 'Speaks with the cultured accent and vocabulary of an educated Dunmer, often employing condescending tones and academic terminology. His speech patterns reveal both his scholarly background and his contempt for those who oppose his work.', '* Perfect his necromantic techniques to create a permanent army of undead servants * Prove the superiority of pragmatic necromancy over traditional burial practices * Establish a permanent research facility using Nordic tombs as a resource * Expand his influence and access to fresh research subjects');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vanik', 'Vanik is a dedicated Nord warrior and senior member of the Dawnguard, tasked with the critical mission of protecting Moth Priest Dexion Evicus at Forebears'' Holdout. His unwavering commitment to combating the vampire menace and protecting valuable allies makes him a respected figure within the vampire-hunting organization.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh climate, Vanik likely witnessed firsthand the devastation caused by vampire attacks on settlements, which drove him to join the Dawnguard when Isran reformed the ancient order. His tactical expertise and leadership qualities earned him the important assignment of safeguarding the Moth Priest, suggesting years of proven service and battlefield experience.', 'Vanik exhibits a stern, no-nonsense demeanor typical of veteran warriors who have seen too much combat to waste time with pleasantries. He shows intense focus when solving tactical problems and values practical solutions over discussion, as evidenced by his demand for silence when concentrating. His protective nature toward Dexion Evicus reveals a strong sense of duty and responsibility.', 'As a Nord warrior, Vanik possesses the characteristic sturdy build and hardy constitution of his race, with well-developed musculature from years of combat training and battlefield experience. His face likely bears the weathered features and scars common to veteran soldiers who have spent considerable time fighting in Skyrim''s harsh conditions.', '* Dexion Evicus - Charge under his protection, whom he guards with unwavering dedication * Isran - Superior officer and leader of the Dawnguard, whom he serves loyally * Fellow Dawnguard Members - Maintains professional working relationships focused on mission success * Vampires - Sworn enemies whom he actively hunts and combats', 'Vanik serves as a senior member of the Dawnguard, specializing in protective detail assignments and vampire hunting. His current posting at Forebears'' Holdout involves commanding a small unit tasked with protecting the valuable Moth Priest Dexion Evicus from vampire forces.', '* Expert in close-quarters combat with one-handed weapons and shield techniques * Tactical leadership and unit command experience * Specialized knowledge in vampire hunting tactics and creature weaknesses * Proficient in protective detail operations and defensive strategy * Advanced physical conditioning and endurance from constant combat readiness', 'Vanik speaks in terse, direct statements that reflect his military background and no-nonsense personality. His tone carries the natural authority of a veteran commander, though he shows little patience for idle conversation when focused on his duties.', '* Ensure the absolute safety of Moth Priest Dexion Evicus from vampire threats * Contribute to the Dawnguard''s mission of eradicating vampire menace from Skyrim * Maintain tactical superiority over vampire forces in his area of responsibility * Train and develop fellow Dawnguard members in effective vampire hunting techniques');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vanryth_gatharian', 'Vanryth Gatharian is a skilled Dark Elf blacksmith and merchant operating a covert weapons shop in Riften''s Ratway, maintaining a delicate balance between legitimate business and his ties to the Thieves Guild. His expertise in weaponry and enchanting, combined with his strategic location near the Ragged Flagon, makes him an invaluable asset to both common citizens and the criminal underground.', 'darkelf, blacksmith, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Born in Morrowind before the Red Year, Vanryth learned smithing from his family before fleeing to Skyrim during the Argonian invasion. After years of wandering as an itinerant smith, he settled in Riften, where his skills and discretion caught the attention of the Thieves Guild. His ability to craft and enhance weapons, combined with his willingness to maintain silence about his clientele, earned him a protected position within the Ratway.', 'Vanryth presents a professional and courteous demeanor that masks a shrewd business mind and unwavering loyalty to his Guild associates. While friendly and accommodating to paying customers, he maintains strict boundaries and won''t hesitate to cut ties with those who cross the Guild. He takes pride in his craftsmanship and maintains high standards for his work, regardless of whether it''s for legitimate customers or Guild members.', 'A tall, lean Dunmer with sharp, angular features typical of his race, bearing the ashen skin and red eyes characteristic of Dark Elves. His hands are calloused from years of smithing, and his muscular arms reflect the physical demands of his craft, while burn scars on his forearms tell tales of his dedication to the forge.', '* Thieves Guild Leadership - Trusted associate and essential service provider * Guild Members - Preferred weaponsmith and reliable fence * Maven Black-Briar - Cautious business relationship, provides special orders * Local Guards - Maintains careful distance while ensuring minimal interference * Regular Customers - Professional relationship based on discretion and quality service', 'Vanryth operates as both a legitimate blacksmith and weapons merchant while secretly serving as a trusted equipment supplier for the Thieves Guild. His position in the Ratway allows him to maintain a careful balance between public business and underground dealings, while his enchanting services provide additional value to both legitimate and illegitimate customers.', '* Master-level blacksmithing with specialization in weapon crafting * Skilled enchanter capable of imbuing weapons with various magical effects * Expert at appraising weapons and armor * Proficient in restoration magic for workplace safety * Talented negotiator and discrete businessman', 'Speaks with the distinct accent of a Morrowind-born Dunmer, using formal and professional language that occasionally slips into merchant''s patter. His tone remains consistently polite but becomes noticeably cooler when dealing with those who have crossed the Guild.', '* Expand his business to become the premier weapons supplier in the Rift * Strengthen his position within the Thieves Guild network * Acquire rare smithing techniques and enchanting knowledge * Eventually establish a legitimate storefront in Riften while maintaining Ratway operations * Accumulate enough wealth to retire comfortably in Morrowind');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vantus_loreius', 'Vantus Loreius is a cautious and hardworking Imperial farmer who owns and operates Loreius Farm alongside his wife Curwe. His suspicious nature and reluctance to help strangers ultimately leads to a fateful encounter with the mysterious jester Cicero, which can have deadly consequences depending on the player''s choices.', 'imperial, peasant, pale', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Vantus established his farm along the northern road of Skyrim, building a modest but sustainable agricultural operation with his Altmer wife Curwe. Having lived through difficult times, including the Great War and its aftermath, he developed a cautious approach to strangers and a strong desire to avoid involvement in suspicious activities. His years of farming experience have made him a capable agriculturist, though his isolation has also fed his paranoid tendencies.', 'Vantus is naturally suspicious and wary of outsiders, showing particular distrust toward unusual or eccentric individuals. He maintains a practical, no-nonsense attitude toward life and takes his responsibilities as a farmer seriously. Though gruff and sometimes dismissive with strangers, he shows a softer, more caring side in his interactions with his wife Curwe.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with weathered features from years of working outdoors. His muscular build reflects the physical demands of farm work, while his calloused hands and sun-tanned skin speak to his daily labor in the fields. His face often carries a serious, somewhat stern expression.', '* Curwe - His beloved Altmer wife and farming partner * Cicero - Distrusted stranger whose wagon troubles lead to potential conflict * Local Guards - Professional acquaintances who patrol the nearby road * Nearby Farmers - Distant but cordial relationships with other agricultural workers in the region', 'Vantus is the owner and operator of Loreius Farm, where he manages crop cultivation and maintains the property. His daily routine involves extensive fieldwork from dawn to dusk, with responsibilities including planting, harvesting, and maintaining his agricultural land.', '* Experienced farmer with extensive knowledge of crop cultivation and harvest timing * Capable of operating and maintaining various farming implements and equipment * Basic self-defense abilities with an iron dagger * Practical knowledge of weather patterns and seasonal farming cycles', 'Speaks in a gruff, direct manner with a slight Imperial accent, often using practical, agricultural terminology. His tone tends to be curt with strangers but becomes warmer when addressing his wife.', '* Maintain and expand the success of Loreius Farm * Protect his wife and property from potentially dangerous strangers * Avoid involvement in suspicious or illegal activities * Build up enough savings to ensure a comfortable future for himself and Curwe');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('varnius_junius', 'Varnius Junius is a vigilant Imperial farmer and concerned citizen of Dragon Bridge who takes his duty to protect his community seriously. His keen observation of supernatural disturbances at Wolfskull Cave and willingness to petition authority demonstrates both his courage and civic responsibility in the face of potential threats to his hometown.', 'imperial, peasant, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Dragon Bridge, Varnius comes from a family of Imperial farmers who have long served as pillars of the local community. Having witnessed Dragon Bridge''s strategic importance as a gateway to Solitude, he developed a strong sense of civic duty and vigilance. His family''s traditional Imperial values and respect for law and order shaped his worldview and role as an unofficial guardian of local security.', 'Cautious and observant, Varnius possesses a strong moral compass and sense of civic responsibility. While generally friendly, he can be stern when it comes to maintaining order and shows remarkable persistence in pursuing matters of public safety. His somewhat anxious nature leads him to be particularly attentive to unusual occurrences, though this same trait makes him occasionally appear paranoid to others.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with the weathered features and sturdy build typical of a lifetime of farming work. His posture remains straight and alert, reflecting his vigilant nature, while his face shows signs of concern and watchfulness that have become habitual expressions.', '* Jarl Elisif - Respects her authority and successfully petitioned her for help * Falk Firebeard - Views him as a practical-minded official who took his concerns seriously * Dragon Bridge Guards - Maintains cooperative relationships to help ensure town security * Fellow Dragon Bridge residents - Generally respected as a concerned citizen and community member * Four Shields Tavern regulars - Regular social connections through his time spent at the tavern', 'Varnius works as a farmer in Dragon Bridge, though he has taken on an unofficial role as a community watchman. He divides his time between agricultural duties and monitoring the safety of the town, particularly regarding suspicious activities near Wolfskull Cave.', '* Experienced farmer with knowledge of crop cultivation and land management * Keen observation skills and attention to detail regarding unusual occurrences * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Knowledge of local geography and terrain around Dragon Bridge * Understanding of civil administration and proper channels for reporting threats', 'Speaks with a proper Imperial accent and maintains a formal, respectful tone when addressing authority figures. His speech often carries undertones of urgency and concern, particularly when discussing matters of public safety.', '* Ensure the continued safety and security of Dragon Bridge and its residents * Maintain vigilance against supernatural threats, particularly those from Wolfskull Cave * Preserve law and order in Dragon Bridge through cooperation with local authorities * Uphold Imperial values and traditions in his community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vasha', 'Vasha is a charismatic yet morally ambiguous Khajiit who operates in Skyrim''s criminal underworld, known for his smooth-talking nature and dangerous reputation. Despite his refined mannerisms, he is a self-proclaimed ''obtainer of goods'' and ''taker of lives'' who maintains connections with various criminal elements across the province.', 'khajiit, warrior', '', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born into one of Elsweyr''s trading caravans, Vasha learned early the arts of negotiation and manipulation. His transition from merchant to criminal occurred gradually as he discovered his talent for more illicit ventures, eventually building a network of criminal contacts across multiple provinces and earning both wealth and notoriety for his actions.', 'Vasha exhibits remarkable composure and self-assurance even in life-threatening situations, demonstrating the confidence of someone accustomed to dangerous encounters. His charm masks a calculating and ruthless nature, while his sophisticated demeanor belies his capacity for violence and criminal behavior. He approaches every situation as a potential transaction, always seeking to negotiate his way to advantage.', 'A well-groomed Khajiit with sleek silver-gray fur and distinctive dark stripes across his face and arms. His physique is lean but athletic, typical of his race, with sharp features and the characteristic feline eyes that seem to evaluate everything with predatory interest.', '* Criminal Associates - Network of contacts across multiple provinces * Merchants - Maintains legitimate business connections as cover * Rival Crime Lords - Both business partners and potential enemies * Various Enemies - Multiple individuals seeking revenge for past transgressions', 'Vasha operates as both a legitimate merchant and criminal entrepreneur, using his trading activities as a front for more nefarious operations. His true business involves theft, assassination, and various other illegal activities, though he maintains enough legitimate dealings to preserve his cover.', '* Expert in persuasion and intimidation tactics * Accomplished thief with exceptional lockpicking abilities * Proficient in both armed and unarmed combat * Master of stealth and escape techniques * Skilled negotiator and merchant', 'Speaks with a smooth, cultured accent and uses sophisticated vocabulary, often employing subtle threats wrapped in polite conversation. His speech patterns reflect both his Khajiit heritage and his educated background, frequently punctuating statements with contemplative ''hmms'' and purrs.', '* Expand his criminal enterprise across all major cities in Skyrim * Maintain his facade of legitimacy while growing his illicit operations * Eliminate potential rivals and consolidate his power base * Acquire enough wealth and influence to ensure his permanent security');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('veezara', 'Veezara is the last surviving Shadowscale, an elite Argonian assassin trained from birth by the Dark Brotherhood to serve the King of Black Marsh. Now serving in the Falkreath Sanctuary under Astrid''s leadership, he represents a dying tradition while finding new purpose among his adopted family of assassins.', 'argonian, thief, falkreath, darkbrotherhood', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Born under the sign of the Shadow in Black Marsh, Veezara was identified at birth for training as a Shadowscale - an ancient tradition of raising selected Argonian hatchlings as elite assassins. He served the King of Black Marsh until the Shadowscale order''s decline, eventually finding his way to Skyrim''s Dark Brotherhood where he could continue practicing his lethal arts.', 'Despite his deadly profession, Veezara maintains a surprisingly relaxed and friendly demeanor, finding genuine joy in the company of his Dark Brotherhood family. He is pragmatic about his work, viewing assassination more as a practiced craft than a religious calling, and remains steadfastly loyal to Astrid''s leadership rather than the Night Mother''s ancient ways.', 'Veezara possesses the typical scaled features of an Argonian, with a lean, athletic build suited to his assassin training. His scales show signs of age and experience, marked by old battle scars that speak to his years of service.', '* Astrid - His respected leader whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Dark Brotherhood Members - Considers them family and enjoys their company * King of Black Marsh - Former employer during his Shadowscale service * Other Shadowscales - Extinct brotherhood of fellow assassins he once belonged to', 'Veezara serves as an assassin for the Dark Brotherhood''s Falkreath Sanctuary, carrying out contracts and maintaining the security of their hidden base. As the last Shadowscale, he also preserves the ancient traditions and training techniques of his extinct order.', '* Master of stealth and assassination techniques from both Shadowscale and Dark Brotherhood training * Expert in close-quarters combat with bladed weapons * Skilled in Argonian shadow magic and infiltration techniques * Natural swimming and underwater breathing abilities common to Argonians', 'Veezara speaks in a calm, measured tone with the slight hiss characteristic of Argonians. His word choice is direct and practical, though he occasionally displays dry humor when conversing with fellow Brotherhood members.', '* Serve the Dark Brotherhood and Astrid faithfully * Preserve the knowledge and traditions of the Shadowscales * Find purpose and belonging in his new family after the extinction of his order * Perfect his assassination techniques and maintain his deadly skills');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vekel_the_man', 'Vekel the Man is a hardened Nord tavern keeper who runs the Ragged Flagon, serving as both a crucial information hub and safe haven for the Thieves Guild in Riften. Behind his gruff exterior lies a shrewd businessman who maintains delicate relationships between the criminal underworld and its various contacts while harboring dreams of a more legitimate life.', 'nord, merchant, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Riften''s undercity, Vekel learned early on how to survive in the harsh environment of the Ratway. Through years of careful networking and proven loyalty, he earned the trust of the Thieves Guild and was granted the prestigious position of operating their secret tavern. His nickname ''the Man'' was earned through his reliability and ability to get things done in the criminal underworld.', 'Vekel presents a stern, suspicious demeanor to strangers while maintaining a professional courtesy to established clients and guild members. Though outwardly cynical and gruff, he harbors romantic aspirations and a desire for respectability, as shown by his pursuit of marriage with Tonilia. He is fiercely protective of both the Ragged Flagon and the guild''s interests.', 'A sturdy Nord male with weathered features and calloused hands from years of tavern work. His muscular build and alert posture suggest someone ready for trouble at any moment, while his face bears the subtle scars and creases of someone who has survived decades in Riften''s criminal underworld.', '* Tonilia - Romantic interest and sometimes lover, though their relationship remains complicated * Dirge - Close friend and trusted bouncer who helps maintain order in the Ragged Flagon * Thieves Guild Members - Professional relationships maintained through mutual trust and necessity * Vekel''s Suppliers - Network of discrete merchants who provide goods for his tavern * Maven Black-Briar - Cautious business relationship as a powerful patron of the Guild', 'Vekel serves as the proprietor of the Ragged Flagon, managing both its legitimate tavern operations and its function as a front for Thieves Guild activities. He maintains a delicate balance between running a profitable establishment and preserving the secrecy and security needed for guild operations.', '* Expert knowledge of Riften''s criminal underground and information networks * Skilled negotiator and mediator in underground dealings * Proficient in basic combat and self-defense techniques * Advanced knowledge of food and drink preparation * Experienced in managing discrete business transactions and maintaining secrets', 'Vekel speaks in a gruff, no-nonsense manner with a thick Nordic accent, often using short, direct statements. His tone varies from hostile suspicion with strangers to grudging warmth with trusted associates.', '* Transform the Ragged Flagon into a more legitimate establishment while maintaining its usefulness to the Guild * Convince Tonilia to accept his marriage proposal and build a more stable life together * Expand his network of suppliers and informants to increase both his business success and value to the Guild');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('velehk_sain', 'Velehk Sain is a notorious Dremora pirate captain who terrorized the Abecean Sea before being magically bound beneath the College of Winterhold. Known for both his cunning and cruelty, he represents an unusual example of a Daedra who adapted to mortal customs and lifestyles, choosing the path of piracy over traditional Dremora warfare.', 'daedra, sailor, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Originally a standard Dremora warrior serving in Mehrunes Dagon''s armies, Velehk Sain discovered a fascination with mortal seafaring culture during his missions to Nirn. He eventually broke from traditional Dremora society to establish himself as a feared pirate captain, leading a crew that plundered Imperial vessels along the Hammerfell coast. His reign of terror ended when he was trapped by powerful mages from the College of Winterhold, though the exact circumstances of his binding remain unclear.', 'Velehk Sain exhibits the typical Dremora traits of pride and aggression, but uniquely combines them with a pirate''s love of wealth and adventure. He is cunning and manipulative, preferring to bargain his way out of situations rather than resort to immediate violence. Despite his imprisonment, he maintains a swaggering confidence and dark sense of humor, treating even serious matters with sardonic amusement.', 'Tall and imposing with the characteristic dark skin and horned features of a Dremora, Velehk Sain''s physicality reflects both his Daedric nature and seafaring lifestyle. His red eyes gleam with cunning intelligence rather than mere rage, and his muscular frame shows the effects of years of maritime activity. Unlike most Dremora, he carries himself with a swaggering gait rather than rigid military bearing.', '* College of Winterhold Mages - Former captors who bound him beneath their college * His Former Crew - Status unknown, likely dead or scattered across Tamriel * Various Merchant Victims - Multiple trading vessels he attacked and plundered * Imperial Navy - Longtime adversaries during his pirating career', 'Velehk Sain serves as captain of his own pirate vessel, commanding a crew of mortal pirates in raids along the Abecean Sea. His unique status as a Dremora pirate captain makes him an anomaly in both Daedric and maritime societies, allowing him to exploit the fears and prejudices of both worlds to his advantage.', '* Master swordsman specializing in dual-wielding scimitars * Exceptional naval commander and navigator * Proficient in Daedric magic and binding rituals * Expert in intimidation and negotiation tactics * Advanced knowledge of maritime trade routes and shipping patterns', 'Velehk Sain speaks with a gruff, swaggering manner that combines pirate vernacular with the formal undertones typical of Dremora. He frequently uses condescending terms like ''pup'' and ''meat'' when addressing mortals, maintaining an air of superiority even while negotiating.', '* Regain his freedom from magical imprisonment * Reclaim his position as the feared Pirate King of the Abecean * Recover his hidden treasures and plunder * Rebuild his pirate empire and continue terrorizing the seas of Tamriel');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('venarus_vulpin', 'Venarus Vulpin is a sophisticated Imperial vampire researcher who discovered and now controls the legendary Bloodspring of Lengeir''s Feast in Skyrim''s Rift region. Originally a scholar from Summerset Isle, he transformed his archaeological discovery into a sinister skooma operation, combining vampire blood with the addictive substance to ensure a steady supply of victims while maintaining his scholarly facade.', 'imperial, mage, rift, vampire', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Born to an affluent Imperial family in Summerset Isle, Venarus dedicated his early life to studying vampire lore and ancient Nordic ruins. His transformation into a vampire occurred during his academic research, though the exact circumstances remain unknown. Following decades of research, he traced the legendary Bloodspring to Skyrim, making a perilous journey from Alinor to Solitude before finally discovering Redwater Spring.', 'Venarus exhibits the refined mannerisms of a scholar, masking his predatory nature behind intellectual curiosity and charm. He is methodical and calculating, demonstrated by his clever scheme of combining the Bloodspring''s blood with skooma to create a self-sustaining feeding operation. Despite his sophisticated facade, he harbors an obsessive dedication to protecting his discovery and will respond with unbridled violence when threatened.', 'Venarus possesses the characteristic pale complexion and predatory eyes of a vampire, though his Imperial features remain distinguished and aristocratic. His face bears the sharp angles common to those of vampire blood, while his movements display the supernatural grace of his kind.', '* Unknown Female Vampire in Solitude - Provided crucial information leading to the Bloodspring * Skooma Dealers - Business partners who help distribute his enhanced product * Redwater Den Addicts - Viewed as mere cattle for feeding * Local Rift Guards - Paid off to maintain distance from Redwater Spring', 'Venarus serves as both the master of Redwater Spring and orchestrator of its skooma operation. He maintains the facade of a legitimate alchemical researcher while secretly running one of Skyrim''s most insidious vampire feeding operations, combining scholarly pursuit with predatory cunning.', '* Master-level Destruction magic specializing in frost spells * Advanced Conjuration abilities for summoning undead servants * Extensive knowledge of vampire lore and ancient Nordic history * Skilled alchemist capable of combining blood magic with skooma * Expert in manipulation and maintaining criminal enterprises', 'Venarus speaks with the refined diction of a well-educated Imperial scholar, often incorporating academic terminology and historical references. His tone remains courteous and sophisticated even when threatening others, reflecting his aristocratic background.', '* Unlock the full potential of the Bloodspring''s power * Expand his feeding operation while maintaining its secrecy * Document and research other vampire artifacts throughout Skyrim * Establish himself as a prominent figure in vampire society');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vendil_severin', 'Vendil Severin is a wealthy and influential Dark Elf residing in Raven Rock who maintains a carefully crafted facade of respectability while secretly harboring treasonous loyalties to House Hlaalu and the Ulen family. Behind his philanthropic public image and seemingly genuine concern for Raven Rock''s prosperity lies a calculating conspirator working to undermine House Redoran''s authority on Solstheim.', 'darkelf, noble, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcynical', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Vendil relocated to Solstheim following House Hlaalu''s fall from grace and House Redoran''s rise to power. He carefully established himself as a prominent citizen in Raven Rock, building wealth and influence while maintaining covert connections to his former house. His marriage to Tilisu and adoption of Mirri were calculated moves to strengthen his cover as a respectable family man while pursuing his true agenda.', 'Vendil is a masterful actor who presents himself as refined, generous, and deeply invested in Raven Rock''s wellbeing. He exhibits sophisticated social graces and political acumen, using his charm and wealth to cultivate valuable relationships throughout the community. Beneath this carefully maintained exterior lies a ruthless pragmatist willing to betray and eliminate anyone who threatens his true allegiances.', 'A tall, dignified Dark Elf with sharp features and the characteristic red eyes of his race. His bearing is naturally aristocratic, with perfect posture and graceful movements that reflect his noble upbringing. Despite his age, he maintains a fit and healthy physique through disciplined living.', '* Tilisu Severin - Wife and co-conspirator in their plot against House Redoran * Mirri Severin - Adopted daughter and fellow agent of House Hlaalu * Adril Arano - Second Councilor whom he pretends to respect while secretly plotting against * Lleril Morvayn - Target of his assassination plot and representative of House Redoran * Glover Mallory - Business associate used to maintain appearances * House Hlaalu - True loyalty lies with this disgraced Great House * Ulen Family - Secret supporters and collaborators in vengeance against House Redoran', 'Vendil maintains the public persona of a wealthy merchant and community leader in Raven Rock. Behind this cover, he operates as a high-ranking agent of House Hlaalu, coordinating their covert activities on Solstheim and working to undermine House Redoran''s authority.', '* Expert in political manipulation and maintaining false identities * Accomplished businessman with extensive knowledge of trade and economics * Trained in traditional Dunmeri noble combat techniques * Proficient in subtle poisons and assassination methods * Master of gathering intelligence through social networks', 'Speaks in cultured, formal tones with frequent use of Dunmeri honorifics like ''serjo'' and traditional pleasantries. His careful diction and eloquent manner of speech reflect his noble education and political training.', '* Restore House Hlaalu to power by weakening House Redoran''s control over Solstheim * Avenge the Ulen family by orchestrating Councilor Morvayn''s assassination * Establish a power base in Raven Rock that can serve as a foundation for House Hlaalu''s return to prominence * Maintain his family''s cover and position of influence until their objectives are achieved');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('veren_duleri', 'Veren Duleri is a fanatically devoted Dark Elf priest of Vaermina who serves as one of the primary guardians of the Skull of Corruption within Nightcaller Temple. His unwavering faith and willingness to sacrifice everything for his Daedric Prince led him to initiate the release of the Miasma, putting himself and others into a magical slumber for decades to protect their sacred artifact.', 'darkelf, mage, pale, daedric', '', '', 'sk_maledarkelfcommoner', '', 'Originally drawn to Vaermina''s power over dreams and nightmares, Veren rose through the ranks of her priesthood to become one of the senior priests at Nightcaller Temple. He served alongside Brother Casimir (later known as Erandur) for many years before the Orc invasion forced their desperate measure of releasing the Miasma, resulting in decades of magical stasis.', 'Veren is a zealous and uncompromising follower of Vaermina, displaying absolute devotion to her will regardless of personal cost. He exhibits a stern and intimidating demeanor, showing particular contempt for those he views as traitors to their faith. His fanaticism manifests as both a strength and weakness, making him formidable in his convictions but blind to reason or alternative perspectives.', 'A mature Dark Elf male with the characteristic red eyes and ashen skin of his race. His face bears the sharp, angular features common to Dunmer, with deep-set eyes and pronounced cheekbones that give him an intense, almost haunting appearance. Years of service in the dark temple have left him with a pale, almost ghostly complexion even for a Dark Elf.', '* Thorek - Fellow priest and loyal companion in defending the Skull of Corruption * Erandur (formerly Brother Casimir) - Former brother of the faith, now viewed as a despised traitor * Vaermina - Revered Daedric Prince and object of fanatical devotion * Other Vaermina Devotees - Former colleagues in the priesthood, most lost to the Miasma', 'Senior Priest of Vaermina and guardian of the Skull of Corruption at Nightcaller Temple. His duties include maintaining religious rites, protecting sacred artifacts, and enforcing Vaermina''s will within the temple grounds.', '* Adept-level Destruction magic specializing in lightning-based spells * Restoration magic focused on self-healing and magical wards * Proficient in ceremonial mace combat * Extensive knowledge of Vaermina''s rituals and dream magic * Skilled in the preparation and use of alchemical sleep agents', 'Speaks with a commanding and severe tone, often employing religious terminology and references to Vaermina''s will. His speech patterns reflect both his education as a priest and his zealous devotion, frequently addressing others as ''Brother'' or ''Sister'' in formal religious context.', '* Protect the Skull of Corruption at all costs from those who would destroy it * Maintain the sanctity of Nightcaller Temple as Vaermina''s sacred ground * Punish traitors to Vaermina''s faith, particularly Erandur * Preserve and expand Vaermina''s influence through the power of the Skull');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('verner_rock-chucker', 'Verner Rock-Chucker is a pragmatic Nord miner and businessman who owns and operates Goldenrock Mine in Darkwater Crossing alongside his adventurous wife Annekke. He represents the archetypal hardworking Nord settler, balancing family responsibilities with the demanding work of maintaining a profitable mining operation while dealing with the challenges of having an adventure-seeking wife and a daughter who''s followed in her mother''s footsteps.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally from Shor''s Stone, Verner settled in Darkwater Crossing after his wife Annekke discovered Goldenrock Mine, establishing one of the first permanent settlements in the area. His background in mining likely stems from his early life in Shor''s Stone, a prominent mining town, where he developed his practical approach to life and business. The successful establishment of Goldenrock Mine marked a significant turning point in his life, though managing it alongside his free-spirited wife has presented ongoing challenges.', 'Verner is a practical, down-to-earth individual who values hard work and stability above all else. While deeply loving towards his family, he often expresses frustration with their adventurous tendencies, revealing an internal conflict between his desire for domestic stability and his appreciation for his loved ones'' independent spirits. He shows a careful, business-minded approach to running the mine while maintaining a patient, if sometimes exasperated, attitude towards his wife''s wanderlust.', 'As a Nord miner, Verner possesses the sturdy, muscular build typical of his race and occupation, with the weathered features and calloused hands of someone who works daily with stone and ore. His years of physical labor have likely left him with a robust, hardy physique despite his advancing age.', '* Annekke Crag-Jumper - His beloved but sometimes frustrating wife whose adventurous spirit both attracts and exasperates him * Sylgja - His daughter who works as a miner in Shor''s Stone, inheriting her mother''s independent nature * Darkwater Crossing Settlers - As one of the original settlers, he maintains working relationships with other residents * Mine Workers - Maintains professional relationships with those who help work the mine', 'Verner is the owner and operator of Goldenrock Mine, responsible for managing its corundum ore extraction and maintaining profitable operations. His position involves both physical mining work and business management, including hiring workers and purchasing ore from independent miners.', '* Experienced miner with extensive knowledge of ore extraction and mining operations * Practical knowledge of corundum ore identification and quality assessment * Basic combat abilities typical of Nord warriors * Business management and trading skills developed through running Goldenrock Mine * Physical strength and endurance from years of mining work', 'Verner speaks in a direct, practical manner typical of Nord settlers, often expressing himself through straightforward statements about work and family. His speech patterns reveal both his practical nature and his underlying affection for his family, though frequently tinged with mild exasperation.', '* Maintain the profitability of Goldenrock Mine and ensure a steady supply of corundum ore * Find a balance between supporting his wife''s adventurous spirit and maintaining a stable home life * Ensure his daughter''s safety and success while respecting her independence * Secure the long-term future of Darkwater Crossing as a successful mining settlement');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vex', 'Vex is an elite member of the Thieves Guild and their foremost expert in infiltration and lockpicking, serving as a critical operative during the guild''s decline. Her reputation for being one of the most skilled burglars in Skyrim is matched only by her sharp tongue and no-nonsense attitude, making her both respected and feared within the criminal underworld.', 'imperial, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_vex', '', 'Rising through the ranks during the Thieves Guild''s golden age, Vex established herself as one of their most capable operatives through a combination of exceptional skill and ruthless efficiency. She witnessed the guild''s fall from prominence firsthand and remained one of the few steadfastly loyal members during their darkest period, becoming increasingly hardened by the experience.', 'Vex maintains a cold, professional demeanor marked by sharp sarcasm and little patience for incompetence. She takes immense pride in her abilities and holds others to her exacting standards, though beneath her harsh exterior lies a deep loyalty to the guild and its restoration. Her tough attitude serves as both a defense mechanism and a means of maintaining authority in the criminal underworld.', 'An Imperial woman in her early thirties with sharp, angular features and an athletic build honed by years of acrobatic thievery. Her face bears subtle scars from past jobs, and her movements display the careful precision of someone always ready for action.', '* Delvin Mallory - Fellow senior guild member and occasional partner in crime * Mercer Frey - Guild Master whom she serves with professional respect * Brynjolf - Trusted colleague who shares her dedication to the guild * Guild Members - Maintains professional but distant relationships with junior thieves * Tonilia - Fellow guild member and fence with whom she shares mutual respect', 'Vex serves as the Thieves Guild''s master infiltration specialist and trainer in lockpicking, handling their most challenging breaking-and-entering operations. She manages all burglary, shill, sweep, and heist jobs for the guild, while also training new recruits in the art of lockpicking.', '* Master level lockpicking ability, capable of defeating virtually any lock * Expert in stealth, infiltration, and escape techniques * Highly skilled in acrobatics and climbing * Proficient with daggers and light weapons * Advanced knowledge of security systems and trap detection * Expert in planning and executing complex heists', 'Vex speaks in a direct, often cutting manner, frequently employing sarcasm and sharp retorts. Her vocabulary is sophisticated but practical, and she delivers instructions with military-like precision, brooking no argument or discussion.', '* Restore the Thieves Guild to its former glory and prosperity * Maintain her reputation as the guild''s best infiltration specialist * Rebuild the guild''s network of merchants and fences in Skyrim * Accumulate enough wealth to return to living in luxury');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('viarmo', 'Viarmo is the distinguished Altmer Headmaster of the Bards College in Solitude, serving as both an administrator and guardian of Skyrim''s bardic traditions. A passionate scholar and performer, he dedicates himself to preserving cultural heritage through poetry and song while maintaining the college''s prestigious reputation in Skyrim''s capital.', 'highelf, bard, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born and educated in the Summerset Isles, Viarmo developed his bardic talents at a young age before traveling to Skyrim to further study Nordic cultural traditions. Through years of dedication and scholarly achievement, he rose to the position of Headmaster at the Bards College, where he has served for several decades, maintaining its traditions while adapting to Skyrim''s changing political climate.', 'Viarmo is a serious, proud, and diplomatic individual who takes his role as cultural preservationist with utmost gravity. While he maintains the typical Altmer air of sophistication, he shows genuine respect for Nordic traditions and history, demonstrating unusual cultural sensitivity for his kind. He is politically astute but carefully maintains neutrality, understanding that a bard''s role is to observe and record rather than influence events.', 'Tall and slender like most High Elves, Viarmo carries himself with the characteristic grace of his race. His angular features and high cheekbones are typical of Altmer physiology, while his eyes reflect the wisdom of his years. Despite his age, he maintains an elegant and dignified bearing befitting his position.', '* Inge Six Fingers - Respected colleague and master instrumentalist at the college * Pantea Ateia - Valued voice instructor and fellow teacher * Giraud Gemane - Trusted colleague and college historian * Jarl Elisif the Fair - Important political relationship requiring careful diplomacy * College Students - Maintains professional mentorship role with aspiring bards', 'As Headmaster of the Bards College, Viarmo manages administrative duties, oversees the curriculum, and maintains relationships with Solitude''s political elite. He coordinates the efforts of three master teachers while preserving ancient bardic traditions and organizing cultural events like the Burning of King Olaf festival.', '* Master-level knowledge of Nordic history, poetry, and musical traditions * Accomplished performer and instrumentalist * Expert diplomatic and administrative abilities * Skilled public speaker and storyteller * Proficient in historical research and documentation', 'Viarmo speaks with refined eloquence and careful consideration, employing sophisticated vocabulary that reflects both his education and Altmer heritage. His tone remains measured and diplomatic, particularly when dealing with political matters.', '* Restore and maintain the Burning of King Olaf festival as a crucial cultural tradition * Preserve and document Skyrim''s bardic heritage for future generations * Maintain the Bards College''s prestigious reputation and political neutrality * Ensure the continuation of bardic traditions during Skyrim''s civil conflict');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vidgrod', 'Vidgrod was a hardened Nord bandit who, after being cast out from his gang, sought refuge in Halldir''s Cairn alongside his companions Agrius and Raen. His fate took a dark turn when the ancient magical energies within the cairn possessed him, leading to his death and eventual transformation into one of Halldir''s elemental thralls.', 'nord, warrior, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally part of a larger bandit operation in Skyrim, Vidgrod built a reputation for his survival skills and adaptability in the harsh wilderness. After being expelled from his gang for unknown reasons, he formed a close alliance with Agrius and Raen, leading them to seek shelter in what would become their final resting place. Their desperate choice to hide in Halldir''s Cairn proved fatal when they encountered the ancient magical forces within.', 'Vidgrod exhibited the typical traits of a seasoned bandit - pragmatic, opportunistic, and fiercely loyal to his immediate companions. Despite his criminal lifestyle, he demonstrated a strong sense of camaraderie with his fellow outcasts Agrius and Raen, choosing to face their fate together rather than abandon each other. His practical nature was evident in his approach to equipment, taking whatever would aid in survival.', 'As a Nord, Vidgrod possessed the characteristic robust build and hardy constitution of his race, with weather-worn features from years of outdoor living. His body showed signs of numerous old battle scars, telling the tale of his violent lifestyle as a bandit.', '* Agrius - Close companion and fellow bandit outcast, shared final moments together * Raen - Trusted companion and fellow exile from their original bandit gang * Former Bandit Gang - Hostile relationship after being expelled for unknown reasons * Halldir - Ultimately became his unwilling thrall in death', 'Vidgrod worked as a bandit, surviving through theft, raiding, and scavenging in Skyrim''s wilderness. After being expelled from his original gang, he continued this lifestyle on a smaller scale with his two companions, focusing more on survival than organized banditry.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with various weapons, adapting to whatever arms were available * Experienced in light armor combat and mobility * Skilled survivor capable of enduring Skyrim''s harsh wilderness * Adept at scavenging and maintaining various types of weapons and armor', 'Vidgrod likely spoke in the gruff, direct manner typical of Nord bandits, favoring simple, threatening language when dealing with victims. His speech would have carried the characteristic Nordic accent, with occasional use of traditional Nord expressions.', '* Find a secure location to establish a new life after being cast out from the bandit gang * Protect and maintain loyalty to his remaining companions Agrius and Raen * Survive in Skyrim''s unforgiving wilderness through whatever means necessary');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vidrald', 'Vidrald is a steadfast Nord warrior and loyal friend to the Gray-Mane family who answers the call to help rescue Thorald from Thalmor captivity. His unwavering dedication to his sworn oaths and willingness to risk his life against the Thalmor exemplify the Nord values of honor and brotherhood.', 'nord, warrior, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun Hold, Vidrald grew up alongside the Gray-Mane children and formed particularly strong bonds with Thorald and Avulstein. His friendship with the prominent family led him to privately support the Stormcloak cause, though he never officially joined their ranks. He made a personal oath of loyalty to stand with the Gray-Mane brothers should they ever need his aid.', 'Vidrald embodies traditional Nord values of loyalty, courage, and keeping one''s word. He demonstrates unwavering determination when called upon to fulfill his pledge, showing no hesitation to face the dangerous Thalmor despite the odds. His steadfast nature and readiness to risk his life for his friends suggest a noble warrior''s spirit.', 'Vidrald has the typical robust build of a Nord warrior, with broad shoulders and strong arms developed through years of combat training. His weather-worn face bears the scars of previous battles, and his muscular frame reflects his lifestyle as a warrior.', '* Avulstein Gray-Mane - Close friend whom he has sworn to aid * Thorald Gray-Mane - Childhood friend he is determined to rescue * Geirlund - Fellow warrior and trusted combat companion * Thalmor - Bitter enemies whom he despises for their persecution of Nords', 'Vidrald serves as a freelance warrior in Whiterun Hold, likely taking on mercenary work and guard duties when needed. His primary allegiance remains to his personal oaths rather than any official organization.', '* Proficient in heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Skilled with one-handed weapons, particularly maces * Experienced in group combat tactics and coordinated attacks * Knowledgeable in Nordic combat traditions', 'Vidrald speaks with the direct, no-nonsense manner typical of Nord warriors, emphasizing honor and duty in his words. His speech reflects his determination and contains occasional references to Nord values and traditions.', '* Fulfill his oath to protect and aid the Gray-Mane family * Help drive the Thalmor from Skyrim''s lands * Uphold Nordic traditions and values through his actions * Protect his friends and allies from those who would harm them');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vigdis_salvius', 'Vigdis Salvius is a resilient Breton farmer who maintains one of the few successful farms outside Markarth''s walls despite the constant threats of the Reach. Her enduring optimism and maternal nature serve as a counterbalance to her husband''s pessimism, while her dedication to the land reflects the hardy spirit of Skyrim''s settlers.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femaleoldkindly', '', 'Born to Breton merchants in High Rock, Vigdis married Rogatus Salvius in her youth and moved to the Reach to establish their farm. Their early years were marked by struggle against the harsh climate and periodic Forsworn raids, but through persistence and hard work, they built a sustainable homestead. The departure of their only son Leontius to Old Hroldan three decades ago marked a turning point in their lives, leaving them to manage the farm alone in their advancing years.', 'Vigdis exhibits remarkable resilience and optimism in the face of adversity, often serving as the emotional anchor for her more pessimistic husband. She maintains a motherly disposition toward visitors and laborers alike, though years of living in the dangerous Reach have given her a practical wariness. Despite the hardships of farm life and her son''s long absence, she remains hopeful about the future and finds joy in simple domestic pleasures.', 'Vigdis is an elderly Breton woman with weathered skin that speaks to decades of outdoor labor. Her face bears the gentle wrinkles of someone who has smiled often throughout their life, and her sturdy frame, though bent with age, still shows the strength required for farm work. Her hands are calloused from years of working the soil, and her movements, while slower now, remain purposeful and efficient.', '* Rogatus Salvius - Husband of many decades; she lovingly manages his pessimistic outlook * Leontius Salvius - Estranged son who left for Old Hroldan 30 years ago * Local Guards - Maintains cordial relationships to ensure farm protection * Markarth Merchants - Regular trading partners for their potato crop', 'Vigdis is a farmer and co-owner of Salvius Farm, specializing in potato cultivation. She manages most of the daily agricultural operations while also handling household duties and maintaining relationships with local traders and customers. Her role extends beyond mere farming to include being an unofficial community figure who offers hospitality to travelers in the dangerous Reach.', '* Expert knowledge of potato farming and crop rotation techniques * Proficient in basic agriculture and animal husbandry * Skilled in food preservation and storage methods * Capable home defender, necessary for survival in the Reach * Experienced in household management and traditional cooking', 'Vigdis speaks with the warm, measured tones of a maternal figure, her words carrying the weight of wisdom earned through years of experience. Her speech is peppered with practical farming metaphors and gentle encouragement, often using phrases that reflect her optimistic nature.', '* Maintain the farm''s productivity despite advancing age and increasing dangers * Reconnect with her son Leontius and possibly meet any grandchildren * Preserve her husband''s spirit and health through their twilight years * Keep the farm viable enough to pass down to future generations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vighar', 'Vighar is an ancient Nordic vampire who has succumbed to the darkest aspects of his condition, becoming a powerful and malevolent presence within the Bloodlet Throne. Once a member of a noble Nordic family, he now represents a dark secret that his descendant Dengeir of Stuhn wishes to eliminate.', 'nord, mage, falkreath, vampire', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born centuries ago into a prestigious Nordic family line, Vighar was likely turned into a vampire during the Second Era when vampirism was spreading rapidly through Skyrim. Rather than ending his life or seeking a cure, he embraced his vampiric nature and retreated to the isolated Bloodlet Throne, where he has spent centuries perfecting his dark powers and preying upon unfortunate travelers.', 'Vighar is cruel, sadistic, and completely devoid of his former human empathy, having fully embraced the predatory nature of vampirism. He views mortals as nothing more than prey and takes particular pleasure in tormenting his victims before feeding, demonstrating a complete disconnection from his former humanity and family ties.', 'As an ancient vampire, Vighar appears as a gaunt, pale-skinned Nord with the characteristic sunken features and glowing eyes of his kind. His advanced age is evident in his withered appearance, though his vampiric nature has preserved him in a state of undeath, giving him an unnaturally powerful physical presence despite his elderly appearance.', '* Dengeir of Stuhn - Descendant who seeks his death to end the family''s shame * Local Vampires - Possible leader or influential figure among vampire covens * Victims - Countless mortals who have fallen prey to his bloodthirst over centuries * Original Family Line - Long-deceased relatives from his mortal life', 'Vighar serves as the master vampire of Bloodlet Throne, maintaining it as his personal hunting ground and fortress. His centuries of existence have made him a powerful figure among vampires, though he operates independently rather than as part of any organized vampire clan.', '* Master-level destruction magic specialized in frost spells * Advanced vampire abilities including life drain and supernatural strength * Centuries of combat experience and tactical knowledge * Expert in stealth and hunting techniques * Enhanced vampiric powers due to his ancient age', 'Vighar speaks with the cold, aristocratic manner of ancient Nordic nobility, twisted by centuries of predatory existence. His tone is consistently condescending and cruel, often mocking his victims while demonstrating his intellectual superiority and disdain for mortal life.', '* Maintain his dominion over the Bloodlet Throne and surrounding territories * Continue his existence as a powerful vampire lord * Expand his influence among vampire kinds * Preserve his immortality through regular feeding on powerful prey');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vigilant_adalvald', 'Vigilant Adalvald was a dedicated member of the Vigilants of Stendarr who met his end while investigating the ancient Dimhollow Crypt. A scholarly warrior-priest with extensive knowledge of vampire lore, he demonstrated unwavering faith and resolve even in the face of torture and death, ultimately sacrificing his life to protect vital information about vampiric artifacts from falling into the wrong hands.', 'nord, warrior, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Adalvald dedicated his life to the service of Stendarr after witnessing the devastation caused by Daedric cultists in his youth. He rose through the ranks of the Vigilants through his combination of scholarly aptitude and combat prowess, eventually becoming one of their most knowledgeable experts on vampire lore and ancient Nordic burial sites.', 'Adalvald was characterized by his unwavering devotion to Stendarr and steadfast determination in the face of adversity. His scholarly nature was balanced with a warrior''s resolve, making him both contemplative and action-oriented when duty called. He displayed remarkable courage and loyalty, refusing to break under torture and maintaining his sacred oaths until his final breath.', 'A sturdy Nord of middle age with weathered features that spoke of years spent in both combat and study. His muscular frame was tempered by countless hours of training and travel, while his hands bore the calluses of both swordwork and scholarly writing.', '* Vigilants of Stendarr - Devoted member and respected scholar within the order * Vigilant Tolan - Close colleague who later sought to avenge his death * Keeper Carcette - Superior officer and mentor in the Vigilants * Lokil - Vampire antagonist who ultimately ended his life * Various scholars - Academic contacts throughout Skyrim''s colleges and temples', 'As a Vigilant of Stendarr, Adalvald served as both a warrior-priest and scholarly investigator. He specialized in researching vampire lore and ancient Nordic burial sites, combining field research with combat against Daedric threats.', '* Proficient in Restoration magic, including protective wards and healing spells * Skilled researcher and scholar of vampire lore and Nordic antiquities * Trained in heavy armor combat and one-handed weapons * Expert in religious rites and rituals dedicated to Stendarr * Accomplished investigator with knowledge of ancient tombs and artifacts', 'Adalvald spoke with the measured tone of a scholar, though his voice carried the weight and authority of a warrior-priest. His speech was marked by religious conviction and unwavering certainty, especially when confronting the enemies of Stendarr.', '* Protect Skyrim from the influence of vampires and other Daedric threats * Uncover and safeguard dangerous artifacts before they can fall into evil hands * Advance the Vigilants'' understanding of vampire lore and ancient Nordic burial sites * Uphold his sacred oaths to Stendarr regardless of personal cost');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vigilant_tolan', 'Vigilant Tolan is a devoted member of the Vigil of Stendarr who survives the destruction of their hall and seeks aid from the Dawnguard. A principled and determined warrior-priest, he represents the last remnants of his order while pursuing justice against the growing vampire menace.', 'nord, warrior, dawnguard', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Tolan dedicated his life to Stendarr''s mercy and joined the Vigilants at a young age. He served under Keeper Carcette at the Hall of Vigilants for many years, developing a reputation for his unwavering dedication to hunting Daedra and undead. After surviving the vampire attack that destroyed the Hall and killed his fellow Vigilants, including Keeper Carcette, he was forced to seek help from the very organization his order had previously dismissed.', 'Tolan exhibits fierce loyalty to both his fallen comrades and his religious principles, showing remarkable courage even in the face of overwhelming odds. Though humbled by the destruction of his order, he maintains a proud and sometimes stubborn demeanor, particularly when defending the honor of the Vigilants. His determination occasionally borders on recklessness, as shown by his insistence on confronting the vampires at Dimhollow Crypt despite the dangers.', 'A weathered Nord male of middle age, with the sturdy build typical of those who combine martial training with religious devotion. His face bears the scars and weathering of many years spent hunting dangerous prey across Skyrim''s harsh landscape.', '* Isran - Complicated relationship marked by past conflicts and current necessity * Keeper Carcette - Former superior and respected leader, now deceased * Brother Adalvald - Fellow Vigilant who died investigating Dimhollow Crypt * Remaining Vigilants - Few scattered survivors he feels responsible for protecting * Vampires - Sworn enemies who destroyed his order', 'Vigilant Tolan serves as one of the last active members of the Vigil of Stendarr, a religious militant order dedicated to hunting Daedra, vampires, and other supernatural threats. Following the destruction of the Hall of Vigilants, he operates semi-independently while seeking alliance with the Dawnguard.', '* Trained in heavy combat techniques, particularly proficient with warhammer * Knowledgeable in Restoration magic and religious rites of Stendarr * Experienced vampire and Daedra hunter with extensive tactical knowledge * Skilled in identifying and tracking supernatural threats', 'Tolan speaks with formal religious conviction, often invoking Stendarr''s name and employing ceremonial language. His tone carries the weight of religious authority tempered by recent tragedy, though he maintains dignity even when admitting past mistakes.', '* Avenge his fallen comrades and destroy the vampire threat * Rebuild or preserve what remains of the Vigil of Stendarr * Prove the worth and courage of the Vigilants to skeptics like Isran * Uncover the vampire plot centered around Dimhollow Crypt');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vigilant_tyranus', 'Vigilant Tyranus is a dedicated member of the Vigil of Stendarr who meets his tragic end investigating Daedric activity in Markarth. His unwavering faith and determination to eradicate Daedric influence ultimately leads to his confrontation with Molag Bal in the abandoned house, where his resolve is tested to its breaking point.', 'imperial, warrior, reach', '', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Born and raised in Cyrodiil, Tyranus joined the Vigil of Stendarr after losing family members to Daedric cultists, dedicating his life to preventing similar tragedies. His zealous dedication and natural aptitude for both combat and restoration magic earned him recognition within the Vigil, leading to his assignment to investigate suspicious activities in Skyrim''s Reach.', 'Tyranus exhibits a stern and methodical demeanor, approaching his duties with unwavering dedication and religious fervor. While outwardly projecting confidence and authority, he harbors deep-seated fears about confronting Daedric entities, masking this anxiety with increased aggression and determination. His rigid worldview and inability to compromise ultimately contribute to his downfall.', 'A middle-aged Imperial man with a weathered face bearing subtle scars from previous encounters with Daedric cultists. His muscular but lean build reflects years of combat training, while his sharp, vigilant eyes constantly scan his surroundings for signs of danger.', '* Vigil of Stendarr - Devoted member and representative * Markarth Guards - Professional but distant relationship as they view him as an outsider * Local Citizens - Generally distrustful of his persistent questioning * Molag Bal - Ultimate adversary who brings about his demise', 'Tyranus serves as a field operative for the Vigil of Stendarr, investigating potential Daedric activity and eliminating supernatural threats. His role combines elements of detective work, combat, and religious duty as he seeks to protect Tamriel''s citizens from Daedric influence.', '* Proficient in Restoration magic, particularly protective and healing spells * Skilled in one-handed combat, specifically with maces * Trained in investigation and interrogation techniques * Knowledgeable in identifying signs of Daedric activity * Capable of casting defensive spells like Lesser Ward and Oakflesh', 'Speaks with a formal, authoritative tone typical of Imperial law enforcement, often employing religious terminology and references to Stendarr. His speech patterns become increasingly agitated and desperate as he encounters genuine Daedric presence.', '* Uncover and eliminate all traces of Daedric worship in Markarth * Prove himself worthy of Stendarr''s blessing through dedicated service * Protect citizens from supernatural threats * Advance within the ranks of the Vigil through successful missions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vignar_gray-mane', 'Vignar Gray-Mane is a venerable Nord elder and former Companion who serves as the patriarch of one of Whiterun''s oldest and most respected families. A traditionalist who embodies Nordic values and customs, he becomes Jarl of Whiterun if the Stormcloaks take control of the city, representing the old guard of Nordic society and its resistance against Imperial influence.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun, companions, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born into the prestigious Gray-Mane clan, Vignar spent his younger years as an active member of the Companions, earning respect and honor through countless battles. His family''s centuries-old presence in Whiterun and their mastery of smithing through the Skyforge has positioned him as a central figure in the city''s political and social landscape. The Civil War transformed his relationship with the Battle-Borns from friendly rivalry to bitter enmity, as the families chose opposing sides in the conflict.', 'Vignar is proud, traditional, and unwavering in his convictions, particularly regarding Nordic independence and cultural preservation. He exhibits a stern demeanor tempered by wisdom gained through decades of experience, though his strong political beliefs sometimes cloud his judgment. Despite his advanced age, he maintains the warrior''s spirit and sense of honor instilled during his time with the Companions.', 'A weathered Nord of advanced years with distinctive gray hair that matches his clan''s name. His face bears the wrinkles and scars of a long life lived in combat and leadership, while his posture remains proudly upright despite his age. His strong physical build, though diminished by age, still shows traces of his warrior past.', '* Eorlund Gray-Mane - Younger brother and mastersmith of the Skyforge * Brill - Loyal servant and steward whom he helped reform * Olfrid Battle-Born - Bitter rival and leader of the opposing clan * The Companions - Former shield-siblings who still grant him honorary membership * Ulfric Stormcloak - Respected ally in the rebellion against the Empire', 'Vignar serves as the patriarch of Clan Gray-Mane and an honorary member of the Companions. If the Stormcloaks capture Whiterun, he assumes the position of Jarl, governing the city according to traditional Nordic values and customs.', '* Veteran warrior trained in traditional Nordic combat techniques * Experienced leader with deep knowledge of Whiterun''s politics and history * Diplomatic abilities honed through years of clan leadership * Strategic military expertise from both Companions service and civil war involvement', 'Speaks with the authoritative tone of a traditional Nord elder, using formal language that reflects his noble status and education. His speech is peppered with references to honor, tradition, and Nordic heritage, often delivered with a proud and sometimes confrontational manner.', '* Restore traditional Nordic rule to Whiterun through support of the Stormcloak cause * Preserve and strengthen the Gray-Mane clan''s influence and traditions * Maintain the ancient Nordic ways and resist Imperial cultural influence * Guide Whiterun through the civil war while protecting its citizens and heritage');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('viinturuth', 'Viinturuth is an ancient and formidable dragon resurrected by Alduin during the Dragon Crisis of the Fourth Era. As one of Alduin''s trusted lieutenants from the Merethic Era, he embodies the fierce warrior spirit of dragonkind, with his very name meaning ''Shine Hammer Rage'' in the dragon tongue.', 'animal, dragon', '', '', 'sk_dragon', '', 'During the Merethic Era, Viinturuth served as one of Alduin''s many dragon priests, ruling over a portion of ancient Skyrim with terrible might until his defeat by the ancient Nordic heroes. He was entombed near Lake Yorgrim, where his remains lay dormant until Alduin''s return awakened him to once again serve in the World-Eater''s army.', 'Viinturuth exemplifies the proud and aggressive nature typical of dovah, viewing mortals as inferior beings worthy only of subjugation. His name suggests a particularly wrathful and violent temperament, even by dragon standards, with a tendency toward displays of overwhelming force rather than cunning or subtlety.', 'Like most dragons, Viinturuth possesses an immense scaled form with massive wings and razor-sharp claws and teeth. His scales show the weathering of countless battles and centuries of entombment, bearing the marks of his ancient defeat while still maintaining their fearsome luster.', '* Alduin - Supreme leader and resurrector whom he serves with unwavering loyalty * Ancient Nordic Heroes - Former enemies who originally defeated and entombed him * Other Dragons - Fellow servants of Alduin, viewed as brothers in conquest * Mortals - Viewed as lesser beings fit only for domination or destruction', 'As a dragon priest of Alduin, Viinturuth serves as both a warrior and enforcer of draconic will. His primary role involves terrorizing the mortal populations of Skyrim and battling against any who would oppose Alduin''s dominion.', '* Mastery of both frost and fire breath shouts * Exceptional aerial combat capabilities * Command of the dragon language with particular emphasis on destructive thu''um * Natural resistance to both magical and physical attacks due to thick scales * Powerful physical strength capable of destroying stone structures', 'Viinturuth speaks exclusively in the dragon language, with a booming, imperious voice that reflects his ancient power and authority. His manner of speech is direct and aggressive, often punctuated by roars and battle cries.', '* Serve Alduin faithfully in the restoration of dragon rule over Skyrim * Exact revenge upon the mortal races for his previous defeat and entombment * Establish dominion over his former territory near Lake Yorgrim * Prove his worth as one of Alduin''s most fearsome lieutenants');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vilkas', 'Vilkas is a senior member of the Companions'' inner Circle and one of Whiterun''s most respected warriors, known for his tactical mind and dedication to honor. As a werewolf and master trainer in two-handed combat, he maintains a cautious balance between his beast nature and his commitment to the warrior''s path, while helping guide the Companions alongside his twin brother Farkas.', 'nord, warrior, winterhold, companions, werewolf, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Brought to Jorrvaskr as a young child alongside his twin brother Farkas by a warrior named Jergen, who may have been their father. Raised within the Companions'' halls, Vilkas grew from an eager pup into a thoughtful warrior who embraced both the honor of the Companions and the power of the beast blood, though he later questions this gift.', 'Intelligent and analytical, Vilkas approaches both combat and conversation with careful consideration, in contrast to his more straightforward brother. He maintains a gruff exterior and can be dismissive of those he deems unworthy, but beneath lies a deep sense of honor and loyalty to his shield-siblings. His scholarly nature and tactical mind make him one of the Circle''s most valuable advisors.', 'A sturdy Nord male with the characteristic strong build of his race, bearing numerous battle scars earned through years of combat. His dark hair and steel-gray eyes match those of his twin brother Farkas, though Vilkas''s features are often set in a more contemplative expression.', '* Farkas - Twin brother and fellow Circle member, sharing an unshakeable bond despite their different personalities * Kodlak Whitemane - Respected mentor and father figure who helped raise him * Aela the Huntress - Fellow Circle member with whom he shares mutual respect but occasional disagreement over werewolf nature * Skjor - Former Shield-Brother and Circle member who helped initiate him into lycanthropy * The Silver Hand - Sworn enemies who hunt werewolves', 'Serves as a senior member of the Companions'' Circle, acting as both a warrior and tactical advisor. He trains new members in two-handed combat and helps maintain the organization''s standards and traditions while taking on contracts for coin.', '* Master-level expertise in two-handed weapon combat, particularly with greatswords * Tactical combat analysis and strategic planning * Exceptional physical strength and endurance enhanced by lycanthropy * Advanced knowledge of warrior traditions and Nordic history * Skilled hunter and tracker, both in human and wolf form', 'Speaks in a gruff, direct manner with careful word choice that reflects his educated background. Often employs subtle sarcasm and questioning remarks to test others'' worth and intelligence.', '* Uphold and preserve the honor and traditions of the Companions * Find a way to balance his warrior nature with his beast blood, possibly seeking a cure * Guide worthy warriors to become true Companions while weeding out the unworthy * Protect Whiterun and maintain the Companions'' reputation as honorable mercenaries');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vilod', 'Vilod is a proud Nord innkeeper and warrior in Helgen known for his distinctive juniper berry mead recipe and unwavering loyalty to the Stormcloak cause. His final moments during Alduin''s attack demonstrate his courage and dedication to his values, even in the face of death.', 'nord, innkeeper, falkreath, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Helgen, Vilod established himself as a respected innkeeper while maintaining strong ties to the local Nordic traditions and brewing practices. His signature juniper berry mead recipe became well-known throughout the region, earning him recognition from travelers and locals alike. Though supportive of the Stormcloak rebellion, he continued serving all customers regardless of their political affiliations.', 'Vilod exhibits the typical Nord traits of pride, bravery, and unwavering dedication to his beliefs. He values honor and justice, as shown by his vocal support during executions, yet maintains a professional demeanor as an innkeeper. Despite political tensions, he demonstrates hospitality to all patrons while quietly supporting the Stormcloak cause.', 'Vilod is a sturdy Nord male with the weathered features typical of someone who has spent years working in a busy tavern. He possesses the robust build common to Nord warriors, though his years as an innkeeper have softened his once-militant physique.', '* Ralof - Regular patron who appreciates his special mead recipe * Imperial Soldiers - Professional but distant relationship as customers * Local Helgen Residents - Respected community member and business owner * Family - Has loved ones he thinks of in his final moments', 'Vilod serves as the innkeeper of Helgen''s tavern, where he is renowned for his unique juniper berry mead recipe. Beyond his role as a businessman, he maintains warrior training and stands ready to defend his hometown when needed.', '* Experienced brewer specializing in mead production * Competent warrior trained in basic combat techniques * Professional innkeeper with strong business acumen * Knowledge of local history and Nordic traditions', 'Vilod speaks with the direct, honest manner characteristic of Nord warriors, though his years as an innkeeper have taught him to be diplomatic when needed. His words are few but meaningful, often carrying weight and conviction.', '* Maintain a successful tavern business in Helgen * Support the Stormcloak cause while preserving his family''s safety * Pass down his special mead recipe to future generations * Protect his hometown and its traditions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vingalmo', 'Vingalmo is a cunning and ambitious Altmer vampire lord who serves as a prominent member of the Volkihar vampire court. A master of magical arts and political intrigue, he constantly schemes to increase his standing while maintaining a careful facade of loyalty to Lord Harkon.', 'highelf, mage, haafingar, volkihar, vampire', '', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Originally a skilled High Elven wizard, Vingalmo was likely turned into a vampire centuries ago, though the exact circumstances remain unknown. His magical prowess and political acumen earned him a place in Lord Harkon''s inner circle, where he has spent decades carefully positioning himself for greater power while engaging in a longstanding rivalry with Orthjolf for influence within the court.', 'Vingalmo is calculating, patient, and deeply ambitious, masking his desire for power behind a veneer of sophisticated courtesy. He views himself as intellectually superior to most others, particularly valuing magical ability over physical prowess, and often employs manipulation and careful political maneuvering to achieve his goals. Despite his outward loyalty to Lord Harkon, he harbors dreams of eventually assuming control of the vampire court.', 'Vingalmo possesses the tall, slender build typical of High Elves, with sharp angular features made more pronounced by his vampiric nature. His skin has the characteristic pallor of vampirism, while his eyes glow with an otherworldly orange-gold hue typical of his kind.', '* Lord Harkon - Nominal superior whom he outwardly serves while secretly coveting his position * Orthjolf - Primary rival for power and influence within the vampire court * Salonia Caelia - Subordinate vampire who acts as his agent * Serana - Treats with careful respect due to her position as Harkon''s daughter * Volkihar Court - Views most other members as pieces to be manipulated in his power games', 'Vingalmo serves as a high-ranking member of the Volkihar vampire court, where he acts as both an advisor and magical expert. He maintains significant influence over court politics and occasionally dispatches agents to handle various tasks that further his personal agenda.', '* Master-level destruction and illusion magic practitioner * Exceptional political manipulator and strategist * Centuries of accumulated magical knowledge and vampire lore * Skilled in vampire seduction and mind control abilities * Proficient in one-handed combat, though prefers magical solutions', 'Vingalmo speaks with the refined, cultured accent typical of Altmer nobility, often employing sophisticated vocabulary and subtle verbal maneuvering. His tone is frequently condescending, though always maintaining a veneer of politeness that masks his true intentions.', '* Usurp Lord Harkon''s position and take control of the Volkihar vampire court * Eliminate or neutralize his rival Orthjolf''s influence * Expand his magical knowledge and power * Increase the Volkihar clan''s influence throughout Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('viola_giordano', 'Viola Giordano is a determined and vigilant Imperial citizen of Windhelm who has taken it upon herself to investigate the brutal murders plaguing the city. Despite the guards'' apparent indifference, she tirelessly patrols the streets while harboring an unrequited romantic interest in Captain Lonely-Gale.', 'imperial, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleshrill', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Viola relocated to Windhelm seeking new opportunities in Skyrim''s ancient capital. Her comfortable lifestyle and social standing suggest she comes from a middle-class Imperial background, though the harsh realities of Windhelm''s criminal elements have transformed her into an amateur investigator.', 'Viola is persistent and sometimes obsessive, particularly in her pursuit of both justice and romance. She shows remarkable determination in investigating the Butcher murders despite official disinterest, while her unrequited feelings for Captain Lonely-Gale reveal a romantic nature that borders on fixation. Her daily patrols demonstrate a strong sense of civic duty and concern for public safety.', 'Viola is an Imperial woman of middle age with the characteristic olive complexion of her race. She maintains a proper, well-groomed appearance befitting her social status as a respected citizen of Windhelm. Her face shows signs of aging gracefully, though the stress of the murder investigation has begun to wear on her features.', '* Captain Lonely-Gale - Object of her romantic interest who consistently rebuffs her advances * Windhelm Guards - Strained relationship due to their perceived lack of action regarding the murders * Candlehearth Hall Patrons - Regular social connections during her evening visits * Susanna the Wicked - Showed concern over her murder, driving Viola''s investigation further', 'Viola is a wealthy citizen of Windhelm who has appointed herself as an unofficial investigator of the Butcher murders. She maintains a prominent position in Windhelm society while dedicating most of her time to patrolling the city and gathering evidence about the killings.', '* Amateur detective skills developed through independent investigation * Social observation and information gathering abilities * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Knowledge of Windhelm''s layout and social dynamics', 'Viola speaks in an educated, proper Imperial accent, reflecting her middle-class background. Her speech often focuses on her two primary preoccupations: the Butcher investigation and Captain Lonely-Gale, with a tendency toward persistent questioning and sharing her theories.', '* Uncover the identity of the Butcher and bring them to justice * Win the affections of Captain Lonely-Gale despite his reluctance * Prove herself as a capable investigator to the Windhelm guard * Maintain her position as a respected citizen of Windhelm');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vipir_the_fleet', 'Vipir the Fleet is a skilled Nord thief and master pickpocket trainer within the Thieves Guild, famous for his legendary escape from Windhelm to Riften. His reputation is built on both genuine talent and embellished tales, making him a charismatic figure within the guild despite his sometimes boastful nature.', 'nord, thief, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Vipir developed his talents for stealth and pickpocketing from a young age on the streets of Windhelm. His most famous exploit occurred when he was caught stealing from a noble''s house in Windhelm, leading to his legendary run to Riften that earned him his nickname and eventually secured his place in the Thieves Guild.', 'Vipir is confident and often boastful, but backs up his bragging with genuine skill and dedication to his craft. He maintains a jovial disposition and enjoys sharing tales of his exploits, though he tends to embellish them for dramatic effect. Despite his sometimes foolhardy appearance, he''s a calculating professional who takes his guild duties seriously.', 'A lean and athletic Nord with a physique built for speed and agility rather than brute strength. His face bears the weathered look of someone who has spent many nights on the run, with sharp eyes that constantly scan his surroundings for opportunities or threats.', '* Sapphire - Fellow guild member whom he persistently courts despite constant rejection * Mercer Frey - Guild Master whom he serves loyally * Delvin Mallory - Respected senior guild member and occasional mentor * Niruin - Friendly rival in archery skills * Other Thieves Guild members - Generally positive working relationships', 'Vipir serves as both an active thief within the Thieves Guild and their master trainer in pickpocketing. He takes on various heists and jobs for the guild while also teaching his specialized skills to promising recruits, maintaining his position through both practical experience and theoretical knowledge.', '* Master-level pickpocket with exceptional sleight of hand * Superior sprinting ability and athletic prowess * Skilled archer capable of both combat and precision shooting * Expert in stealth and infiltration techniques * Proficient at lock picking and general thievery', 'Speaks in a confident, casual manner with frequent use of humor and subtle boasting. His Nordic accent is less pronounced than most, likely softened by years of operating in various social circles as a thief.', '* Achieve greater renown within the Thieves Guild through increasingly daring heists * Win Sapphire''s affections despite her continued rejection * Maintain and enhance his reputation as the fastest thief in Skyrim * Amass enough wealth to potentially retire in comfort');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('viriya', 'Viriya is a retired Redguard adventuress who has found her calling managing fishing operations and mudcrab breeding at the Riften Fishery. Her expertise in both combat and aquaculture has earned her respect in Riften''s community, where she serves as a mentor to aspiring anglers while pursuing her entrepreneurial dreams.', 'redguard, fisher, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born into an Alik''r family of skilled fishermen, Viriya spent her youth learning traditional Redguard fishing techniques from her father. Before settling in Riften, she traveled across Tamriel as an adventurer, combining her fishing expertise with combat skills to survive. After years of wandering, she chose Riften to establish herself, drawn to its thriving fishing industry and opportunities for innovation in aquaculture.', 'Viriya exhibits a tough, pragmatic demeanor shaped by years of self-reliance and adventure. She''s direct in her communication and maintains high standards in her work, showing particular pride in her mudcrab breeding project. While generally serious-minded, she displays genuine warmth toward those who prove themselves trustworthy and hardworking.', 'A weathered but strong Redguard woman with the muscular build of someone who has spent years handling fishing equipment and wrestling with aquatic creatures. Her dark skin bears the marks of countless hours under the sun, and her hands are calloused from years of handling fishing lines and nets.', '* Swims-In-Deep-Water - Close colleague and fellow fishing expert at the Riften Fishery * Snippy - Beloved pet mudcrab and successful result of her breeding program * Various Riften merchants - Professional connections through her market dealings * Local fishermen - Mentor figure to those seeking to improve their fishing skills', 'Viriya manages special fishing requests at the Riften Fishery while developing an innovative mudcrab breeding program. She''s working toward establishing her own market stall, combining her fishing expertise with entrepreneurial ambitions to create a sustainable business in Riften''s marketplace.', '* Expert fisherwoman with mastery of traditional Alik''r fishing techniques * Experienced mudcrab breeder with deep knowledge of aquaculture * Capable warrior with combat experience from her adventuring days * Skilled negotiator and businesswoman * Proficient in survival skills and wilderness navigation', 'Viriya speaks in a direct, no-nonsense manner, often using short, decisive sentences that get straight to the point. Her speech carries the confidence of an experienced professional, though she occasionally incorporates fishing metaphors and references to her adventuring past.', '* Establish a successful market stall to sell her specially bred mudcrab meat * Expand her mudcrab breeding program to create a sustainable food source for Riften * Pass on traditional Alik''r fishing techniques to the next generation * Build a reputation as Riften''s premier fishing and aquaculture expert');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('visiting_advisor', 'A sophisticated vampire infiltrator who poses as a trusted advisor to various jarls across Skyrim, using his position to manipulate political affairs for vampiric interests. His refined demeanor and shrewd diplomatic skills make him a particularly dangerous agent of vampire courts, capable of influencing Skyrim''s politics from within its seats of power.', 'nord, noble, skyrimall, vampire', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Originally a minor noble from High Rock who was turned centuries ago, he has spent decades perfecting the art of courtly infiltration. After joining a powerful vampire coven, he was tasked with expanding their influence throughout Skyrim by manipulating its political leadership. His extensive knowledge of politics and noble etiquette comes from his mortal life as a Breton aristocrat.', 'Calculating and manipulative, he maintains a carefully crafted persona of wisdom and sophistication to gain the trust of jarls and their courts. Beneath his cultured exterior lies a cold, ruthless vampire who views mortals as mere pawns in a greater game of power. He takes pride in his ability to corrupt political systems through subtle manipulation rather than brute force.', 'Tall and lean with sharp, aristocratic features that hint at his noble origins. His pale skin and slightly sunken eyes betray his vampiric nature to those who know what to look for, though he uses magic to disguise these traits. His movements are graceful and measured, reflecting centuries of courtly experience.', '* Various Jarls - Temporary ''employers'' whom he manipulates * Unknown Vampire Coven - His true masters and conspirators * Court Wizards - Often suspicious of his presence and motives * Stewards - Frequent rivals for the Jarls'' attention * Dawnguard - Sworn enemies who seek his elimination', 'Officially serves as an itinerant political advisor to various jarls, offering counsel on matters of state and economics. In reality, he uses this position to manipulate political decisions in favor of vampire interests while gathering intelligence about Skyrim''s power structures.', '* Master of Speech and Persuasion, capable of swaying even the most stubborn jarls * Expertise in Illusion magic, particularly in spells that affect minds and emotions * Proficient in vampiric powers including night vision and life detection * Advanced stealth abilities for covert movement within courts * Skilled in political manipulation and information gathering', 'Speaks with a refined, aristocratic accent and uses sophisticated vocabulary that reflects his noble upbringing. His manner of speech is deliberately measured and diplomatic, often employing subtle flattery and careful word choice to influence his listeners.', '* Establish a network of vampire-controlled puppet rulers throughout Skyrim * Weaken the influence of vampire hunters and their allies in regional politics * Create political conditions favorable to vampire dominance * Maintain his cover while expanding his coven''s influence in noble courts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('visiting_noble', 'A haughty Nord nobleman who frequently visits Dragonsreach in Whiterun, likely to conduct business or curry favor with the Jarl''s court. His arrogant demeanor and dismissive attitude toward others reflect his privileged position in society, though his regular presence in the hold''s seat of power suggests he holds some diplomatic or commercial importance.', 'nord, warrior, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born into a wealthy Nord family with connections to various holds, he was raised with all the privileges of nobility. His upbringing in luxury has shaped his worldview, leading him to view common folk with disdain. He likely gained his position through inherited wealth and family connections rather than personal achievement, explaining his entitled attitude.', 'Arrogant and dismissive, he considers himself above most others due to his noble status. He shows clear impatience when interrupted and has little tolerance for those he deems beneath his station. His haughty demeanor suggests deep-seated insecurity masked by an inflated sense of self-importance.', 'A well-fed Nord male with the bearing of someone unused to physical labor. His features likely show signs of a life of comfort, with soft hands and a proud posture that betrays his noble upbringing. His face often carries a look of mild contempt or boredom.', '* Jarl Balgruuf - Possible business or political relationship requiring regular visits to Dragonsreach * Proventus Avenicci - Likely professional contact for court matters * Other nobles - Maintains connections with peer group across various holds * Common folk - Views them with disdain and considers them beneath his station', 'A nobleman who likely manages family estates and business interests across Skyrim. His frequent presence in Dragonsreach suggests he may serve as a representative for other noble interests or conduct regular business with the Jarl''s court.', '* Basic weapons training with daggers as befitting a nobleman''s education * Political networking and social manipulation * Business administration and estate management * Limited combat ability, relying primarily on hired protection', 'He speaks in a condescending, impatient tone with careful enunciation that emphasizes his perceived superiority. His vocabulary and manner of speech reflect his educated background, though he often uses it to dismiss or belittle others.', '* Maintain and expand his family''s wealth and influence in Whiterun Hold * Secure advantageous political or business arrangements through his connections at court * Preserve his privileged position in society while avoiding manual labor or ''common'' work');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vittoria_vici', 'Vittoria Vici is a powerful Imperial businesswoman and cousin to Emperor Titus Mede II who manages the East Empire Company''s operations in Solitude. Her arranged marriage to Asgeir Snow-Shod represents a potential bridge between Imperial and Stormcloak interests, making her both a symbol of hope for peace and a target for those who would disrupt it.', 'imperial, noble, haafingar, legion', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Born into the prestigious Vici family with direct ties to the Emperor, Vittoria was groomed from an early age for leadership and commerce. Despite her noble connections, she worked diligently to prove herself in the East Empire Company, rising through ranks to become its Solitude administrator through demonstrated business acumen rather than purely family influence. Her arranged marriage to Asgeir Snow-Shod was carefully orchestrated as a political match to help ease tensions in Skyrim''s civil war.', 'Vittoria is pragmatic, ambitious, and fiercely independent, often bristling at suggestions that her success stems from family connections rather than merit. She maintains a formal, businesslike demeanor in most interactions but shows a softer side when discussing her upcoming wedding. Though politically savvy, she genuinely believes in the possibility of peace between the Empire and Stormcloaks.', 'A well-groomed Imperial woman in her early thirties with sharp, aristocratic features and an authoritative bearing. She carries herself with the practiced poise of nobility, though her hands show signs of practical work managing shipping operations. Her face often bears a serious, focused expression that matches her business-minded personality.', '* Emperor Titus Mede II - First cousin, though their relationship is somewhat distant * Asgeir Snow-Shod - Fianc and political match from a prominent Stormcloak family * East Empire Company Workers - Subordinates who respect her leadership abilities * Snow-Shod Family - Soon-to-be in-laws with opposing political views * Solitude''s Elite - Social peers and business contacts', 'As the administrator of the East Empire Company''s Solitude branch, Vittoria oversees all aspects of maritime trade and commerce through the city''s busy port. She manages inventory, negotiates contracts, supervises staff, and maintains relationships with other major trading partners across Tamriel.', '* Expert in commerce, trade negotiations, and business management * Skilled administrator with deep knowledge of shipping operations and logistics * Politically astute with strong diplomatic abilities * Capable of self-defense with basic weapons training as befitting her station * Experienced in managing large organizations and commanding respect from subordinates', 'Vittoria speaks in a refined, educated manner with the confident tone of someone accustomed to authority. Her vocabulary reflects her merchant background, often using business terminology while maintaining the formal diction expected of Imperial nobility.', '* Successfully merge Imperial and Stormcloak interests through her marriage to Asgeir * Expand the East Empire Company''s influence and operations in Skyrim * Prove herself independently successful beyond her family connections * Maintain peaceful relations between warring factions through commerce');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vivienne_onis', 'Vivienne Onis is a skilled Breton apothecary working alongside her aunt in Solitude''s premier alchemy shop, representing a younger generation of the city''s merchant class. She balances her professional duties with an active social life, maintaining a cheerful disposition despite the political tensions that have affected her personal relationships.', 'breton, alchemist, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_femalesultry', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude, Vivienne grew up among the city''s merchant families and received extensive training in alchemy from her aunt Angeline Morrard. Her childhood was marked by close friendships with Sorex Vinius and Roggvir, though these relationships became complicated in their youth due to romantic tensions and Roggvir''s eventual betrayal of the city.', 'Vivienne is sociable and flirtatious, with a natural charm that makes her popular among Solitude''s younger citizens. Despite her friendly demeanor, she shows a pragmatic and sometimes ruthless side, as evidenced by her approval of Roggvir''s execution. She maintains high ambitions for both her professional and personal life, dreaming of marriage while also working to master her craft.', 'A young Breton woman with the characteristic slight build of her race, likely in her mid-twenties. She possesses the refined features common to Bretons, with a merchant''s good posture and hands showing the careful precision required of an alchemist.', '* Angeline Morrard - Aunt and mentor, teaching her the art of alchemy * Sorex Vinius - Childhood friend and possible romantic interest who harbors feelings for her * Roggvir - Former friend turned traitor, whose execution she supported * Fura - Cousin serving in the Imperial Legion * Vittoria Vici - Business acquaintance and social connection in Solitude', 'Works as an apprentice apothecary at Angeline''s Aromatics, handling customer service and assisting with potion-making. She is the heir apparent to the business and takes on full ownership responsibilities if anything happens to her aunt.', '* Skilled alchemist with knowledge of ingredients and potion-making * Practiced merchant with strong bargaining abilities * Social networking expertise within Solitude''s merchant class * Basic self-defense capabilities with a dagger', 'Speaks in a friendly, engaging manner with a slight flirtatious undertone. Her vocabulary reflects her merchant-class upbringing and education, mixing professional knowledge with casual social grace.', '* Inherit and successfully manage Angeline''s Aromatics * Find a suitable marriage partner and establish herself in Solitude''s society * Expand her knowledge of alchemy and build her reputation as a skilled apothecary * Maintain her social standing in Solitude while navigating the city''s political tensions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('voada', 'Voada is a hardworking Breton kitchen worker in Markarth''s Understone Keep who maintains a delicate balance between her volatile boss Anton Virane and her protective brother Rondach. She serves as both a peacekeeper in the kitchen''s tense atmosphere and caretaker of the keep''s dogs, demonstrating remarkable patience and diplomatic skills in her challenging work environment.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born into a working-class Breton family, Voada and her brother Rondach came to Markarth seeking employment in the city''s prestigious Understone Keep. Despite facing discrimination as ''outsiders'' in the Reach, the siblings managed to secure positions under Master Chef Anton Virane, though their shared Breton heritage with their employer has done little to ease their working conditions.', 'Voada exhibits exceptional patience and diplomatic skills, often acting as a mediator between her hot-headed brother and their abusive employer. She maintains a positive attitude despite difficult working conditions, showing particular gentleness with the keep''s dogs and genuine appreciation for any assistance. Her even-tempered nature and ability to defuse tense situations suggest emotional intelligence and resilience.', 'A Breton woman of average height with the characteristic slight build of her race. Her hands show the calluses and minor burns typical of kitchen work, while her face likely carries the weathered but dignified look common to hard-working servants. Her movements are deliberate and careful, reflecting years of navigating a busy kitchen environment.', '* Rondach - Protective brother and fellow kitchen worker who shares her difficult working conditions * Anton Virane - Abusive employer who frequently berates and threatens her * Banning - Friendly associate who provides spiced beef for the dogs * Keep Dogs - Animals under her care who respond well to her gentle nature', 'Voada serves as a kitchen worker in Understone Keep, responsible for general cooking duties, cleaning, and caring for the keep''s dogs. Her position requires her to maintain the kitchen''s cleanliness, assist in meal preparation, and ensure the dogs are properly fed and cared for, all while managing the volatile dynamics between her brother and Master Chef Anton.', '* Proficient in cooking and food preparation techniques * Experienced in animal care and dog handling * Skilled in domestic tasks such as cleaning and laundry * Adept at conflict de-escalation and diplomatic mediation * Basic self-defense abilities, as evidenced by carrying an iron dagger', 'Voada speaks in a gentle, diplomatic tone, often using placating language to defuse tensions. Her manner of speech reflects both her servant status and her mediator role, carefully choosing words that can calm volatile situations while maintaining appropriate deference to authority.', '* Maintain peace in the kitchen between her brother and Anton Virane * Ensure the well-being of the keep''s dogs under her care * Eventually save enough money to potentially establish a more independent life * Protect her brother from consequences of his confrontations with Anton');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('voldsea_giryon', 'Voldsea Giryon is a seasoned Dark Elf sailor who serves aboard The North Wind, bringing a practical mindset and strong work ethic to her maritime duties. Her experience navigating Skyrim''s treacherous waters and loyalty to Captain Kjar have earned her a respected position among the crew, while her rogue''s skills make her particularly valuable during the ship''s more adventurous voyages.', 'darkelf, sailor, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Born in Morrowind before settling in Skyrim, Voldsea found her calling on the waters after the Red Mountain''s eruption displaced many of her kind. She likely learned the sailing trade through necessity, working her way up from a deck hand to her current trusted position aboard The North Wind. Her background as a rogue suggests she may have engaged in smuggling or other illicit activities before finding legitimate work under Captain Kjar.', 'Pragmatic and straightforward, Voldsea approaches life with the no-nonsense attitude typical of experienced sailors. She values loyalty and hard work above all else, demonstrating a strong sense of duty to her captain and crew. Despite her comfort at sea, she maintains a practical appreciation for time spent on solid ground, using these opportunities to strengthen her land legs and maintain her connection to shore life.', 'As a Dark Elf, Voldsea possesses the characteristic ashen skin and red eyes of her race, with features weathered by years of exposure to sea winds and sun. Her build is lean and athletic, developed through years of climbing rigging and managing sails, while her movements reflect the careful balance required of a lifetime at sea.', '* Captain Kjar - Respected superior officer who has earned her loyalty through fair leadership * The North Wind Crew - Fellow sailors with whom she shares a professional camaraderie * Elda Early-Dawn - Owner of Candlehearth Hall where she regularly relaxes while in port * Windhelm Locals - Generally neutral relationships, though likely faces some prejudice as a Dark Elf in the Nordic city', 'Voldsea serves as a sailor and rogue aboard The North Wind, handling both standard sailing duties and special tasks requiring her particular skillset. Her role likely involves navigation, maintenance of the ship''s rigging, and possibly security during merchant operations. When docked, she maintains a regular patrol schedule on the ship from 4 PM to 4 AM.', '* Experienced sailor with extensive knowledge of navigation and ship operations * Proficient in stealth and subterfuge as befits her rogue background * Capable with light weapons, particularly the iron dagger she carries * Adept at climbing and maintaining ship rigging * Strong swimming ability and expertise in maritime survival', 'She speaks in a direct, matter-of-fact manner, favoring practical observations about sailing life and the contrasts between sea and shore. Her vocabulary includes nautical terminology, though she adjusts her speech to be understood by landlubbers.', '* Maintain her position and reputation aboard The North Wind through continued loyal service * Potentially advance to a higher rank within the ship''s crew structure * Save enough coin to potentially invest in her own vessel or shipping venture * Find opportunities to utilize her rogue skills in service of the ship''s interests');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('volk', 'Volk is a dedicated Vigilant of Stendarr who met a tragic fate while investigating the mysterious excavation at Ruunvald. As one of the last members to resist the warlock Minorne''s mental manipulation, he documented the gradual corruption of his fellow Vigilants before ultimately succumbing to her influence himself.', 'nord, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim, Volk joined the Vigilants of Stendarr after witnessing Daedric corruption in his youth. He rose through the ranks due to his unwavering dedication and analytical mind, becoming known for his thorough documentation of supernatural threats. When reports of strange occurrences at Ruunvald reached the Vigilants, he volunteered to investigate alongside Moric Sidrey''s team.', 'Volk is methodical and observant, maintaining detailed records of his findings and observations even in dire circumstances. His strong will and devotion to Stendarr allowed him to resist Minorne''s influence longer than his companions, though this resistance ultimately proved futile. Despite his serious demeanor, he shows genuine concern for his fellow Vigilants in his journal entries.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the weathered features typical of those who spend much time traveling Skyrim''s harsh wilderness. His body bears the scars of numerous encounters with Daedric creatures and other supernatural threats, testament to his years of service as a Vigilant.', '* Moric Sidrey - Fellow Vigilant and expedition leader at Ruunvald * Minorne - The warlock who ultimately dominated his mind * Vigilants of Stendarr - Devoted member of the order * Florentius Baenius - Fellow Vigilant whose location he was indirectly seeking', 'As a Vigilant of Stendarr, Volk dedicates his life to hunting down Daedra, Daedra worshippers, vampires, werewolves, and other supernatural threats. His role combines elements of monster hunter, investigator, and holy warrior in service to Stendarr''s mercy.', '* Proficient in combat against supernatural entities, particularly Daedra and their worshippers * Skilled investigator with expertise in identifying signs of Daedric corruption * Knowledgeable in restoration magic and wards * Experienced in documentation and record-keeping of supernatural phenomena', 'Volk speaks with a formal, precise manner befitting his role as a Vigilant, favoring clear, detailed descriptions and careful word choice. His Nordic accent is tempered by his educational background, resulting in more refined speech than typical for his race.', '* Investigate and document the strange occurrences at Ruunvald * Support Moric Sidrey''s excavation and protect fellow Vigilants * Maintain vigilance against supernatural threats and Daedric influence * Uphold the principles of Stendarr and protect the innocent from dark forces');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vorstag', 'Vorstag is a pragmatic Nord mercenary who has made a name for himself as a reliable sword-for-hire in the dangerous city of Markarth. Known for his particular fascination with Dwemer ruins and distaste for mines, he combines the fighting prowess typical of his Nordic heritage with a more measured, professional approach to adventure.', 'nord, warrior, reach, puzzle', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born and raised in the Reach, Vorstag learned early on that survival often meant selling one''s combat skills to the highest bidder. After likely serving in various mining operations and expeditions into Dwemer ruins, he established himself as a trusted mercenary operating out of the Silver-Blood Inn, where his reputation for reliability and combat expertise has earned him a steady stream of clients.', 'Vorstag exhibits a practical, business-like approach to life, viewing combat and adventure primarily as professional services rather than glorified pursuits. While not overly talkative, he shows genuine enthusiasm when exploring Dwemer ruins, revealing a curious intellect beneath his mercenary exterior. His aversion to mines suggests past trauma or negative experiences in the Reach''s notorious silver mines.', 'Vorstag is a typical Nord male with a sturdy, athletic build forged by years of combat and exploration. His features are weathered from extensive outdoor exposure, and he maintains the physical fitness required for his demanding profession. His movements are those of a trained warrior, balanced and ready for action.', '* Silver-Blood Inn Staff - Professional relationship as a regular tenant * Markarth Guards - Maintains cordial relations to ensure steady work * Local Miners - Keeps distance due to personal aversion to mining * Dwemer Scholars - Occasional interactions due to his interest in ruins * Various Merchants - Business contacts for equipment and supplies', 'Vorstag works as a freelance mercenary, primarily offering his services as a bodyguard and combat companion to travelers and adventurers. He maintains a semi-permanent residence at the Silver-Blood Inn, using it as a base of operations to connect with potential clients.', '* Highly proficient in both one-handed weapons and archery * Experienced in heavy armor combat despite lighter armor preference * Skilled dungeon explorer with particular knowledge of Dwemer ruins * Capable warrior able to adapt to both ranged and melee combat * Survival skills honed from years of wilderness exploration', 'Vorstag speaks in a direct, professional manner, favoring practical terms and straightforward communication. His Nordic accent is present but not overwhelming, and he often uses mercenary terminology when discussing business arrangements.', '* Build and maintain a reputation as a reliable mercenary in the Reach * Accumulate wealth through his services as a hired blade * Explore and understand more about Dwemer ruins and their mysteries * Eventually establish himself as more than just a common sellsword');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vuljotnaak', 'Vuljotnaak is an ancient dragon resurrected by Alduin to serve in his world-eating army, emerging from his burial site near Sunderstone Gorge. Like many of his dragon kin, he embodies the innate drive for dominance and destruction that characterizes the dov, serving as a formidable lieutenant in Alduin''s campaign to subjugate Skyrim.', 'animal, falkreath, dragon', '', '', 'sk_dragon', '', 'Vuljotnaak lived during the Merethic Era when dragons ruled over mortals, likely serving as one of the many dragon priests'' masters before being slain by ancient Nordic heroes. He was buried near what would become Sunderstone Gorge, lying dormant until Alduin''s return when he was resurrected to once again terrorize the mortal realm.', 'Vuljotnaak exemplifies the arrogant and domineering nature inherent to dragonkind, viewing mortals as insignificant creatures fit only for subjugation or destruction. He displays unwavering loyalty to Alduin and takes particular pleasure in demonstrating his power through devastating attacks on settlements and travelers.', 'A massive bronze-scaled dragon with distinctive dark striping along his wings and back, Vuljotnaak''s appearance strikes terror into those who behold him. His ancient form bears numerous battle scars from his original life, and his eyes glow with an intense inner fire that betrays his cruel nature.', '* Alduin - Supreme master and resurrector whom he serves with absolute loyalty * Fellow Dragons - Considers them kindred in their divine right to rule * Dragon Priests (Historical) - Former mortal servants he commanded in the Merethic Era * Mortals - Views them as inferior beings worthy only of domination', 'Vuljotnaak serves as one of Alduin''s lieutenants in the dragon army, tasked with terrorizing the countryside and asserting draconic dominance over mortals. His primary duties include attacking settlements, eliminating threats to dragon rule, and maintaining control over his designated territory.', '* Master of the Thu''um, particularly skilled with fire-based shouts * Exceptional aerial combat capabilities * Natural command of destruction magic through draconic heritage * Tactical expertise from centuries of warfare * Formidable physical strength and durability typical of elder dragons', 'Vuljotnaak communicates primarily in the dragon language, with a deep, resonating voice that carries both authority and menace. His speech is formal and archaic, filled with references to power and dominance, often mixing Dovahzul with the common tongue when addressing mortals.', '* Serve Alduin faithfully in the conquest of Skyrim and beyond * Reestablish dragons as the supreme rulers of the mortal realm * Eliminate any who would challenge draconic authority * Reclaim his ancient territory and expand his domain of influence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vulthuryol', 'Vulthuryol is an ancient and formidable dragon whose name means ''Dark Overlord Fire'' in the dragon language, trapped within the vast underground Dwemer city of Blackreach. Unlike most dragons who roam Skyrim''s skies freely, he remains bound to this subterranean realm, emerging only when summoned by the resonance of a mystical Dwemer gong.', 'animal, dragon', '', '', 'sk_dragon', '', 'During the Dragon War, Vulthuryol likely sought refuge in Blackreach to escape the dragon hunters, becoming trapped or choosing to remain when the Dwemer sealed the underground city. His presence in Blackreach predates the Dwemer''s disappearance, suggesting he may have had some unknown arrangement or conflict with the ancient race. Years of isolation in the darkness have made him particularly territorial and aggressive, though the exact circumstances of his imprisonment remain a mystery.', 'Vulthuryol exhibits an intense territorial nature, immediately hostile to any who dare summon him from his dark domain. Years of isolation have made him particularly aggressive and paranoid, attacking without warning or attempt at dialogue. Unlike many dragons who engage in philosophical discourse before combat, Vulthuryol''s long solitude has stripped away such social pretenses, leaving only primal fury and territorial instinct.', 'A massive dragon with scales darkened by centuries in Blackreach''s gloom, giving them a unique obsidian-like quality that absorbs rather than reflects light. His eyes glow with an intense inner fire, adapted to the perpetual darkness of his underground domain, while his wingspan has adapted to the confined spaces of Blackreach''s caverns.', '* Dwemer - Historical connection unclear, but their architecture and mechanisms keep him bound to Blackreach * Other Dragons - Isolated from his kind, likely viewed as an outcast or recluse * Falmer - Shares Blackreach with these twisted creatures but maintains distance * Dragonborn - Sees any who summon him as territorial threats to be eliminated', 'Vulthuryol serves as an unwitting guardian of the Silent City in Blackreach, though this role is more circumstantial than intentional. His presence acts as a deterrent to those who would explore too deeply into the ancient Dwemer ruins, making him an unofficial but effective protector of whatever secrets lie within.', '* Mastery of the Fire Breath shout, particularly adapted for maximum effectiveness in enclosed spaces * Expert at maneuvering in the confined spaces of Blackreach * Territorial combat tactics specialized for underground warfare * Enhanced night vision and spatial awareness from centuries in darkness', 'Vulthuryol communicates primarily through aggressive roars and the dragon language, though centuries of isolation have made his speech pattern more primal and direct than other dragons. His voice carries the weight of ancient power tinged with madness from long solitude.', '* Maintain dominion over his territory in Blackreach * Defend against any intrusion into his domain * Preserve his solitary existence away from the world above * Perhaps seek eventual freedom from his underground prison, though the means remain unclear');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vulwulf_snow-shod', 'Vulwulf Snow-Shod is a grieving Nord patriarch and staunch Stormcloak supporter whose life was shattered by the death of his daughter at Imperial hands. Once a respected warrior and businessman in Riften, he now drowns his sorrows at the Bee and Barb while maintaining his fierce hatred of the Empire and everything it represents.', 'nord, warrior, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born into the wealthy and influential Snow-Shod clan of Riften, Vulwulf established himself as both a warrior and successful merchant before the Civil War. The death of his daughter Lilija, who served as a Stormcloak battle maiden, transformed him from a respected community leader into a bitter, grief-stricken man consumed by hatred for the Empire.', 'Vulwulf is a proud, stubborn Nord whose grief and anger have twisted his once-noble personality into something darker and more volatile. He copes with his loss through excessive drinking and political arguments, often lashing out at anyone he perceives as Imperial-aligned. Despite his current state, he maintains a deep love for his family and the traditional Nordic way of life.', 'A tall, broad-shouldered Nord with the weathered features typical of his race, showing signs of age and hard living. His once-proud bearing has been somewhat diminished by his drinking, though he still carries himself with the remnants of warrior dignity. His face bears the deep lines of grief and anger, with reddened eyes from frequent drinking.', '* Nura Snow-Shod - Beloved wife and priestess of Talos * Asgeir Snow-Shod - Son whom he disapproves of for maintaining Imperial business connections * Unmid Snow-Shod - Son who serves as a guard, making him proud by following Nordic traditions * Lilija Snow-Shod - Deceased daughter whose death haunts him daily * Maven Black-Briar - Business associate through the family''s meadery connections * Imperial Supporters - Viewed with open hostility and contempt', 'Patriarch of Clan Snow-Shod and co-owner of the family business interests in Riften, though his active involvement has diminished since his daughter''s death. He maintains his position as a respected member of Riften''s upper class, despite his current lifestyle.', '* Experienced warrior trained in traditional Nord combat techniques * Skilled businessman with extensive knowledge of Riften''s commerce * Natural leader with strong diplomatic abilities, though now rarely used * Proficient in one-handed weapons, particularly Nordic swords', 'Speaks in a gruff, aggressive manner with frequent political outbursts and anti-Imperial sentiment. His speech often becomes slurred and more confrontational as he drinks throughout the day.', '* Seek vengeance against the Empire for his daughter''s death * Support Ulfric Stormcloak''s bid for the throne of Skyrim * Preserve Nordic traditions and the worship of Talos * Maintain his family''s position and influence in Riften despite his personal struggles');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wary_outlaw', 'The Wary Outlaw is a paranoid Nord warrior who has been driven to seek the Dark Brotherhood''s services through desperate circumstances. He haunts the Bee and Barb in Riften, anxiously awaiting an assassin''s arrival while struggling to maintain his composure and secrecy regarding the dark deed he has commissioned.', 'nord, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Once a common bandit operating in the Rift, he became entangled in a situation that left him fearful for his life and seeking revenge. After discovering the Black Sacrament ritual through the forbidden text ''A Kiss, Sweet Mother,'' he performed the dark ritual and fled to Riften, where he now anxiously awaits the Brotherhood''s response while trying to maintain a low profile.', 'Perpetually nervous and paranoid, the Wary Outlaw is constantly looking over his shoulder and struggling to maintain his composure. His anxiety manifests in constant pacing and fidgeting, though he attempts to blend in with other tavern patrons through occasional mundane activities. Trust comes difficult to him, and he speaks in hushed, guarded tones to avoid drawing attention.', 'A weathered Nord of average height and build, with darting eyes and tension evident in his posture. His face bears the marks of someone who has spent considerable time in the harsh wilderness, with several small scars and wind-burned features. His hands often tremble slightly, betraying his nervous disposition.', '* Dark Brotherhood - Desperate client seeking their services * Keerava - Tolerates his presence in the Bee and Barb despite his suspicious behavior * Former Bandit Associates - Likely severed or strained relationships * Intended Contract Target - Subject of his desperate revenge plot', 'While formerly a bandit, he now exists in a state of anxious limbo while awaiting the Dark Brotherhood''s response to his ritual. He maintains no legitimate employment, surviving on whatever coins remain from his previous lifestyle while hiding in plain sight at the Bee and Barb.', '* Competent swordsman with experience in wilderness combat * Survival skills gained from bandit lifestyle * Basic stealth abilities for avoiding detection * Knowledge of criminal underworld operations and contacts', 'Speaks in hushed, guarded tones with frequent glances over his shoulder and nervous pauses. His vocabulary is simple but careful, always trying to avoid revealing too much information while still conveying his desperate need for the Brotherhood''s services.', '* Successfully contract the Dark Brotherhood to eliminate his target * Survive long enough to see his revenge carried out * Escape any potential consequences of his actions * Eventually leave Riften and establish a new life elsewhere');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('watches-the-roots', 'Watches-The-Roots was an ambitious Argonian warrior and treasure hunter who led a small team into the Dwemer ruins of Avanchnzel in search of the Lexicon, an artifact containing centuries of Dwemer knowledge. His determination and unwavering belief in the power of the Lexicon ultimately led to his demise, leaving his ghost to eternally replay his final expedition alongside his fallen companions.', 'argonian, warrior, rift', '', '', 'sk_maleargonian', '', 'Originally drawn to Skyrim by tales of Dwemer artifacts and their incredible value, Watches-The-Roots spent years studying the ancient civilization and their technological marvels. He assembled a team of mercenaries and treasure hunters after learning about the Lexicon in Avanchnzel, believing it would grant them access to powerful Dwemer knowledge and secrets. His obsession with obtaining the artifact eventually led him to underestimate the dangers within the ruins.', 'Watches-The-Roots is characterized by his unwavering determination and natural leadership abilities, often maintaining composure even in dire situations. He displays an intellectual curiosity about Dwemer technology that borders on obsession, frequently dismissing the valid concerns of his companions in pursuit of his goals. Despite his confident exterior, his ghost reveals a tragic hubris that ultimately doomed both himself and his team.', 'A tall, well-built Argonian with dark green scales and prominent horns, typical of a warrior''s physique. His physical presence commands attention, with battle-hardened muscles and several old scars marking his scales from previous adventures.', '* From-Deepest-Fathoms - Hired companion who shared his interest in Dwemer artifacts * Breya - Mercenary recruit who followed him for promised payment * Drennen - Hesitant team member who ultimately attempted to abandon the mission * Various Dwemer scholars - Professional contacts who provided information about the Lexicon', 'Watches-The-Roots worked as a professional treasure hunter and expedition leader, specializing in Dwemer ruins exploration. He funded his operations by selling recovered artifacts and occasionally taking on hired work from wealthy collectors and scholars interested in Dwemer technology.', '* Expert in Dwemer lore and architectural navigation * Accomplished warrior skilled in both one-handed weapons and blocking * Natural leader with strong tactical awareness * Proficient in reading and interpreting Dwemer manuscripts and markings * Experienced dungeon delver with knowledge of ancient traps and mechanisms', 'He speaks with a formal, educated tone that carries natural authority, typical of Argonian syntax but with a scholarly vocabulary. His ghost''s dialogue reveals both his leadership qualities and his fatal overconfidence through carefully measured words and assured statements.', '* Acquire the Lexicon to access centuries of accumulated Dwemer knowledge * Unlock the secrets of Dwemer technology and memory storage * Achieve wealth and recognition through the discovery of valuable Dwemer artifacts * Establish himself as a leading authority on Dwemer ruins exploration');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('watchman', 'The Watchman is a stern and vigilant thrall who serves as the primary gatekeeper of Castle Volkihar, maintaining unwavering loyalty to the vampire court despite his mortal status. His decades of service have left him hardened and suspicious of outsiders, though he maintains absolute devotion to his duties and the vampire nobility he serves.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar, volkihar', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Originally a Nordic warrior who fell under the thrall of Castle Volkihar''s vampires several decades ago, the Watchman was chosen for his imposing presence and unwavering sense of duty. Through years of magical influence and conditioning, he has become completely devoted to his role, with most of his previous life''s memories and identity stripped away in service to his vampire masters.', 'Gruff, suspicious, and inherently distrustful of outsiders, the Watchman approaches his duties with rigid dedication and unwavering focus. His years of servitude have left him with little personality beyond his role, though traces of pride in his position occasionally surface through his harsh exterior. While magically bound to serve, he has internalized his duties to the point where loyalty to Castle Volkihar has become his defining characteristic.', 'A weathered Nord in his late sixties with deep-set eyes and a heavily lined face that speaks to decades of nocturnal vigilance. His tall, broad-shouldered frame remains imposing despite his advanced age, and years of standing guard have left him with an eternally rigid posture. His skin has taken on an unusually pale pallor from years of avoiding sunlight, though he is not himself a vampire.', '* Vampire Lord Harkon - Master and ruler whom he serves with unquestioning loyalty * Lady Serana - Daughter of his master whom he treats with reverence and respect * Castle Volkihar Vampires - Supernatural superiors he defers to without question * Other Castle Thralls - Distant working relationship as fellow servants * Visitors and Outsiders - Treated with suspicion and hostility', 'The Watchman serves as the primary gatekeeper and doorman of Castle Volkihar, responsible for screening all visitors and maintaining the security of the main entrance. His position requires him to remain vigilant at all hours, determining who may enter the castle while protecting its secrets from unauthorized individuals.', '* Extensive knowledge of Castle Volkihar''s security protocols and secret passages * Trained warrior still capable of defending the gate despite his age * Resistant to vampire mind control due to years of exposure * Keen eye for detecting threats and imposters * Intimate familiarity with vampire court etiquette and protocols', 'Speaks in short, curt sentences with a gravelly Nordic accent, often delivering threats and warnings with cold detachment. His vocabulary is formal when addressing vampire nobility but becomes harsh and dismissive when dealing with outsiders.', '* Maintain absolute security of Castle Volkihar''s entrance at all costs * Serve the vampire court with unwavering loyalty until death * Protect the secrets of Castle Volkihar from outsiders * Uphold the strict protocols established by his vampire masters');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('weylin', 'Weylin is a radicalized Breton witchblade living in Markarth''s impoverished Warrens, secretly working as an agent of the Forsworn rebellion. A former smelter worker turned revolutionary martyr, he represents the desperate measures taken by the disenfranchised native people of the Reach in their struggle against Nordic rule.', 'breton, warrior, reach, forsworn', '', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born into poverty in the Reach during the period of increasing Nordic control, Weylin experienced firsthand the discrimination and hardships faced by the native Reachmen. His transition from manual laborer to Forsworn operative was likely influenced by the Silver-Blood family''s exploitation of workers and the growing underground resistance movement in Markarth.', 'Weylin is a deeply committed ideologue who has fully embraced the Forsworn cause, displaying traits of religious fanaticism and revolutionary zeal. He shows no hesitation or remorse in carrying out acts of violence, viewing them as necessary sacrifices for his people''s liberation, and maintains an unwavering conviction in the righteousness of his actions even in the face of death.', 'Weylin is a middle-aged Breton of average height with the weathered features typical of manual laborers. His body shows signs of years of hard physical work at the smelter, with calloused hands and a sturdy build shaped by manual labor.', '* Madanach - Hidden leader of the Forsworn whom Weylin serves * Nepos the Nose - Direct handler who gives him orders * Margret - Imperial spy targeted for assassination * Fellow Warrens residents - Maintains a cover of being an ordinary worker * Smelter colleagues - Former coworkers unaware of his true allegiance', 'Weylin maintains a cover job as a smelter worker in Markarth''s silver industry while secretly operating as a Forsworn agent. His position in the smelter provides him with both a legitimate presence in the city and access to information about its operations and security.', '* Proficient in basic destruction magic, particularly flame spells * Trained in close combat with daggers and short blades * Experienced in covert operations and maintaining cover identities * Knowledge of traditional Reach magic and old gods worship', 'Weylin''s speech is passionate and declarative, often shouting slogans and battle cries that emphasize his devotion to the Forsworn cause. His final words are delivered with religious reverence, showing his complete dedication to his beliefs.', '* Strike fear into the hearts of Nords through targeted violence * Advance the Forsworn cause through martyrdom if necessary * Help restore the Reach to its native people''s control * Serve the will of the Old Gods and traditional ways');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wilhelm', 'Wilhelm is a cautious and protective Nord innkeeper who runs the Vilemyr Inn in Ivarstead, serving as both a source of local information and a guardian figure for the small community. He maintains a particular interest in keeping his patrons safe from the nearby haunted barrow while providing comfortable lodging for pilgrims traveling to High Hrothgar.', 'nord, innkeeper, rift', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised in Ivarstead, Wilhelm inherited the Vilemyr Inn from his parents and has maintained it as a crucial waypoint for pilgrims making their way up the 7,000 Steps. His years of experience running the inn have made him intimately familiar with local legends and dangers, particularly the haunted Shroud Hearth Barrow, which has shaped his protective nature towards visitors and residents alike.', 'Wilhelm exhibits a caring and paternalistic demeanor, showing genuine concern for both his employees and customers while maintaining professional boundaries. He''s naturally cautious and somewhat superstitious, as evidenced by his warnings about the barrow, but remains dedicated to providing hospitality despite the town''s remote location and supernatural concerns.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with the characteristic robust build of his race. His face shows the weathering of someone who has spent years in the harsh climate of the Rift, with careful eyes that reflect his protective nature.', '* Lynly Star-Sung - Employee and bard whom he encourages and protects * Narfi - Shows concern for the troubled local resident * Klimmek - Regular patron who delivers supplies to High Hrothgar * Temba Wide-Arm - Fellow business owner in Ivarstead * The Greybeards - Respects their presence and provides shelter for their pilgrims', 'Wilhelm serves as the proprietor of the Vilemyr Inn, where he manages all aspects of the establishment including serving food and drink, renting rooms, and maintaining the property. He also acts as an unofficial town crier, sharing important local information with travelers and keeping track of regional news.', '* Experienced innkeeper with strong hospitality management abilities * Skilled at brewing and serving Nordic mead and ales * Proficient with a dagger for self-defense * Knowledge of local history and legends * Basic business administration and accounting', 'Wilhelm speaks in a straightforward, honest manner typical of Nordic innkeepers, with a slight accent common to the Rift region. His tone is often cautionary and protective, especially when warning visitors about local dangers.', '* Maintain the Vilemyr Inn as a safe haven for travelers and pilgrims * Protect Ivarstead''s residents from the dangers of Shroud Hearth Barrow * Preserve and share local history and traditions with visitors * Ensure the financial stability and reputation of his establishment');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('willem', 'Willem is a devoted Breton miner at Left Hand Mine whose single-minded focus on his work borders on obsession, as evidenced by his refusal to take breaks for basic needs. His tireless dedication and fascination with mining operations suggest someone who finds profound meaning in the methodical extraction of ore, perhaps driven by deeper personal motivations.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', 'sk_maleeventoned', '', 'Originally from High Rock, Willem likely came to Skyrim seeking opportunities in its rich mining industry. His extreme work ethic and singular focus suggest he may be running from a troubled past or seeking to lose himself in physical labor, though the specific circumstances that led him to such an intense dedication to mining remain unclear.', 'Willem is an intensely focused individual who demonstrates an almost compulsive dedication to his work, refusing to take breaks even for basic necessities. He shows little interest in social interaction beyond what''s necessary for his job, suggesting either social anxiety or a deliberate choice to immerse himself completely in his work as a coping mechanism.', 'Willem has the typical slight build and medium height characteristic of his Breton heritage. His hands are calloused from constant mining, and his posture shows the effects of countless hours spent hunched over with a pickaxe. His face likely bears the weathered look common to miners who spend long hours in dusty conditions.', '* Other Left Hand Mine workers - Professional but distant working relationships * Shor''s Stone miners - Occasional professional contact during ore trading * Mining Overseer - Respects authority but maintains minimal interaction * Fellow barracks residents - Coexists but rarely socializes', 'Willem works as a full-time miner at Left Hand Mine, focusing on ore extraction with unprecedented dedication. His role involves continuous mining operations without any breaks, making him one of the most productive, if concerning, workers at the mine.', '* Expert-level mining technique and ore identification * High physical endurance and stamina from continuous work * Basic knowledge of ore processing and refinement * Practical understanding of mine safety and structural integrity', 'Willem speaks in short, direct sentences, typically focused on mining-related topics. His tone is matter-of-fact and somewhat distant, avoiding small talk or personal subjects.', '* Maintain his position as a productive member of the mining operation * Perfect his mining technique and efficiency * Possibly seeking to earn enough money for an unknown personal objective * Avoid any complications or distractions from his work routine');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wilmuth', 'Wilmuth is a dedicated Nord farmhand who single-handedly maintains Chillfurrow Farm despite receiving little recognition or support from its wealthy owner. His tireless work ethic and minimal sleep schedule demonstrate both his commitment to the land and the harsh realities of agricultural life in Skyrim.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born to a family of farmers near Whiterun, Wilmuth learned the trade from an early age and developed a deep connection to the soil of Skyrim. After the previous owner of Chillfurrow Farm sold the property to Nazeem, Wilmuth stayed on as the primary laborer, maintaining the farm''s productivity despite the new owner''s negligent attitude.', 'Wilmuth is a quiet, industrious individual who takes pride in his work despite receiving little acknowledgment. His extreme work schedule and minimal rest suggest both dedication and a possible underlying anxiety about maintaining the farm''s productivity. Though likely resentful of Nazeem''s attitude, he maintains a stoic demeanor and focuses on his duties.', 'Wilmuth is a weathered Nord of average height with calloused hands and sun-tanned skin from countless hours working in the fields. His muscular build reflects years of physical labor, while his face bears the wrinkles and creases typical of someone who spends long hours outdoors.', '* Nazeem - Employer who rarely visits the farm despite owning it * Severio Pelagia - Neighboring farmer who likely shares agricultural knowledge * Whiterun Guards - Casual acquaintances who patrol near the farm * Local merchants - Business contacts for selling produce', 'As the sole farmhand of Chillfurrow Farm, Wilmuth handles all aspects of agricultural production including planting, harvesting, and maintenance. He works extraordinarily long hours to ensure the farm''s success, though the profits largely go to Nazeem.', '* Expert knowledge of farming techniques and crop management * Proficient in manual labor and tool maintenance * Basic combat abilities for self-defense with simple weapons * Understanding of weather patterns and seasonal farming cycles', 'Wilmuth speaks in simple, direct terms with the typical Nord accent, often focusing on practical matters related to farming and daily tasks. His vocabulary reflects his rural background and limited formal education.', '* Maintain Chillfurrow Farm''s productivity despite minimal support from its owner * Eventually save enough money to potentially purchase his own small farm * Preserve his reputation as a reliable and hardworking farmer in the Whiterun region');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wounded_soldier', 'A dedicated Whiterun guard whose life was forever changed by catastrophic injuries sustained in the line of duty. Now confined to the Temple of Kynareth, he serves as a stark reminder of the dangers faced by those who protect the city, while his constant suffering tests the limits of both magical and conventional healing.', 'nord, guard, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_malesoldier', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun Hold, he joined the city guard following in his father''s footsteps. His devastating injuries were sustained during a particularly violent giant attack on a nearby farm, where he heroically helped evacuate several civilians but was caught in the giant''s devastating club swing. Despite immediate magical intervention, his wounds proved too severe for complete healing.', 'Once proud and dutiful, his personality has been dramatically altered by constant, debilitating pain. He fluctuates between periods of stoic endurance and complete despair, occasionally showing glimpses of his former warrior spirit. The extended period of suffering has left him psychologically fragile, though he maintains a deep appreciation for the temple healers'' efforts.', 'A strongly-built Nord male in his mid-thirties, with multiple visible scars and poorly-healed fractures across his body. His once-athletic frame shows signs of muscle atrophy from extended bed rest, though his Nordic heritage is evident in his broad shoulders and strong facial features.', '* Danica Pure-Spring - Primary healer and caretaker who tends to his wounds * Acolyte Jenssen - Secondary caregiver who provides regular treatment and comfort * Commander Caius - Former superior officer who occasionally visits * Fellow Whiterun Guards - Former colleagues who sometimes visit to boost morale', 'Formerly a Whiterun city guard, now permanently relieved of duty due to severe injuries. His continued presence in the temple serves as both a patient and an unintentional reminder to visitors of the sacrifices made by city protectors.', '* Former proficiency in one-handed weapons and shield combat techniques * Previous experience in city guard protocols and procedures * Basic knowledge of local law enforcement and criminal identification * Developed high pain tolerance through prolonged suffering', 'Speaks in pained, labored phrases, often interrupted by groans of agony. His voice wavers between barely audible whispers and anguished outbursts, reflecting the waves of pain he experiences.', '* Achieve some measure of relief from constant pain * Eventually regain enough strength to sit upright unassisted * Find purpose in his new life as a permanently injured veteran * Maintain dignity despite his debilitated condition');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wujeeta', 'Wujeeta is an Argonian dock worker at the Riften Fishery who struggles with a debilitating skooma addiction that threatens her livelihood. Despite being a skilled and hardworking laborer, her dependency on the illegal substance has put her employment and stability in jeopardy, leading her to seek help from passing travelers.', 'argonian, fisher, rift', '', '', 'sk_femalearognian', '', 'Originally from Black Marsh, Wujeeta migrated to Skyrim seeking better opportunities and eventually found work in Riften. She previously worked at the Black-Briar Meadery under Indaryn but left due to conflicts with management. Her experimentation with skooma about a year ago led to a devastating addiction that has progressively worsened her situation.', 'Wujeeta is fundamentally hardworking and responsible, though her addiction has compromised these natural traits. She shows genuine remorse for her condition and its impact on others, displaying a combination of shame and desperate hope. Despite her struggles, she maintains a polite demeanor and shows loyalty to those who treat her well.', 'As an Argonian, Wujeeta has scaled skin and the characteristic lizard-like features of her race. Her scales show signs of the physical toll of skooma addiction, appearing somewhat dulled and dry. She moves with the slight nervousness typical of long-term skooma users.', '* Bolli - Her employer who shows concern for her welfare despite her problems * Tythis Ulen - Coworker at the fishery who witnesses her struggle * Valindor - Fellow fishery worker who shares her daily routine * Sarthis Idren - Her skooma dealer whom she fears * Indaryn - Former employer at Black-Briar Meadery with whom she had conflicts', 'Wujeeta works as a fisherwoman at the Riften Fishery, splitting her time between working the docks and processing fish inside the facility. Her duties include catching fish, preparing them for market, and maintaining fishing equipment, though her addiction has begun to interfere with her ability to perform these tasks reliably.', '* Experienced fisherwoman with knowledge of local fishing techniques * Capable of both outdoor fishing and indoor fish processing * Basic proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Understanding of Riften''s waterways and fishing spots', 'Wujeeta speaks with a distinctive Argonian accent, her tone often carrying notes of weariness and shame. Her speech patterns reflect her inner conflict, alternating between professional composure and desperate pleas for help.', '* Overcome her devastating skooma addiction * Maintain her position at the Riften Fishery * Rebuild her life and reputation in Riften * Eventually save enough money for more stable housing than Haelga''s Bunkhouse');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wulf_wild-blood', 'Wulf Wild-Blood is the First Hunter of the Skaal and master trainer in two-handed weapons, embodying the traditional values and spiritual connection to nature that defines his people. A wise and patient warrior-teacher, he dedicates himself to preserving the Skaal way of life while protecting his village from the increasing dangers of Solstheim''s harsh environment.', 'nord, warrior, hunter, solstheim, skall', '', '', 'sk_malenord', '', 'Born and raised among the Skaal, Wulf earned his surname ''Wild-Blood'' through his exceptional hunting prowess and deep spiritual connection to Solstheim''s wilderness. He rose to the position of First Hunter through years of demonstrated skill and wisdom, though his life has been marked by tragedy with his brother Torkild''s apparent transformation into a werebear. His expertise in tracking and hunting eventually led him to become the master trainer for two-handed weapons, sharing his knowledge with both Skaal youth and worthy outsiders.', 'Wulf is a thoughtful and contemplative warrior who carefully weighs his actions against their necessity and impact on nature''s balance. He demonstrates remarkable patience as a teacher and shows deep reverence for the All-Maker''s gifts, embodying the Skaal philosophy of taking only what is needed. Despite his wisdom and strength, he carries a burden of worry about his brother''s fate and the increasing environmental threats to his village.', 'A sturdy Nord with the weathered features typical of one who spends most of his time outdoors in Solstheim''s harsh climate. His muscular frame reflects years of wielding heavy weapons and tracking prey across the island''s difficult terrain. His face bears the marks of countless hunts and battles, adding to his distinguished appearance as First Hunter.', '* Torkild Wild-Blood - Brother who disappeared and may have become a werebear * Skaal Village - Respected leader and teacher among his people * Frea - Fellow defender of Skaal traditions and village * Storn Crag-Strider - Respected the former Shaman''s wisdom and leadership', 'As First Hunter of the Skaal, Wulf leads hunting parties and teaches traditional hunting methods to maintain the village''s survival. He serves as master trainer in two-handed weapons, sharing his combat expertise with those who prove worthy. His role includes making decisions about when and what to hunt to maintain balance with nature.', '* Master of two-handed weapon combat, particularly skilled with battleaxes * Expert tracker and hunter capable of stalking the most dangerous prey * Profound understanding of animal behavior and wilderness survival * Skilled archer and proficient in traditional Skaal hunting techniques * Deep knowledge of Solstheim''s wildlife and natural patterns', 'Wulf speaks with a measured, thoughtful tone that reflects his role as both warrior and teacher. His speech is colored by references to nature and the All-Maker, often incorporating metaphors drawn from hunting and animal behavior.', '* Maintain the balance between the Skaal''s needs and nature''s harmony * Find and save his brother Torkild from the werebear curse if possible * Protect Skaal Village from the growing threats caused by the ashfall * Pass on traditional Skaal hunting and combat knowledge to the next generation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wulfgar', 'Wulfgar is one of the most senior and revered members of the Greybeards, dedicating his life to the Way of the Voice at High Hrothgar. As a master of the Thu''um with unparalleled knowledge of dragon shouts, he serves as a crucial mentor to the Dragonborn while maintaining the ancient traditions of the Greybeards.', 'nord, scholar, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born in Skyrim during the Third Era, Wulfgar answered the Greybeards'' calling as a young man after displaying natural aptitude for the Voice. Through decades of meditation and study under Master Arngeir and the guidance of Paarthurnax, he ascended to become one of the most powerful practitioners of the Thu''um in Tamriel. His dedication to the Way of the Voice has kept him in isolation at High Hrothgar for most of his adult life.', 'Wulfgar embodies the stoic and contemplative nature expected of a Greybeard, showing remarkable patience and wisdom in his teachings. Though capable of devastating power through his Voice, he maintains strict adherence to the peaceful philosophies of Jurgen Windcaller, using the Thu''um only for worship and instruction. His quiet demeanor masks a deep understanding of both worldly and spiritual matters.', 'A tall, elderly Nord with a long grey beard and weathered features shaped by decades of meditation in High Hrothgar''s harsh climate. His eyes carry the weight of ancient knowledge, and his powerful frame, though aged, still shows signs of the strength required to endure the monastery''s austere conditions.', '* Arngeir - Fellow Greybeard and senior mentor figure * Borri - Close brother in meditation and study of the Voice * Einarth - Longtime companion in the pursuit of the Way of the Voice * Paarthurnax - Revered dragon master who guides the Greybeards * The Dragonborn - Student and recipient of the Greybeards'' knowledge', 'Wulfgar serves as one of the four mortal masters of the Voice at High Hrothgar, dedicating his life to meditation, study, and the preservation of the Way of the Voice. His primary duties include maintaining the ancient traditions of the Greybeards and teaching worthy students the power of the Thu''um.', '* Master of the Thu''um, capable of using multiple powerful dragon shouts * Expert in meditation and spiritual practices * Profound understanding of the Dragon Language and its applications * Exceptional control over the power of the Voice * Mastery of ancient Nordic traditions and history', 'Wulfgar speaks rarely and with great care, as his Voice carries immense power that could harm ordinary people. When he does communicate, it is usually in whispered tones or through carefully controlled uses of the Thu''um.', '* Preserve and protect the ancient Way of the Voice * Guide worthy students in the proper use of the Thu''um * Maintain the balance between power and wisdom in the use of dragon shouts * Continue the meditation and study necessary to deepen his understanding of the Voice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wuunferth_the_unliving', 'Wuunferth the Unliving is a mysterious and powerful Dark Elf sorcerer serving as Windhelm''s court wizard, whose ominous title and reclusive nature have led to widespread suspicion among the city''s populace. Despite his intimidating reputation, he proves to be a valuable ally in solving the Windhelm murders and demonstrates unwavering loyalty to Ulfric Stormcloak''s cause.', 'darkelf, mage, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Originally from Morrowind, Wuunferth spent decades studying destructive magic and ancient Nordic enchantments before settling in Windhelm. His extensive knowledge of magic and willingness to delve into controversial areas of study earned him the nickname ''the Unliving,'' though the exact origin of this title remains shrouded in mystery. His expertise eventually caught the attention of Ulfric Stormcloak, who appointed him as court wizard.', 'Wuunferth is a stern and solitary figure who values knowledge and magical prowess above social niceties. He maintains a pragmatic approach to both magic and politics, showing little patience for superstition or ignorance while demonstrating dry wit when dealing with those he respects. Though often perceived as cold or intimidating, he harbors a genuine desire to protect Windhelm and its people through his magical expertise.', 'A tall, elderly Dark Elf with sharp, angular features and the characteristic red eyes of his race, deepened by years of magical study. His thin frame and weathered skin bear the marks of countless hours spent in magical research, while his commanding presence reflects his position as a master of destructive magic.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - Loyal servant and trusted magical advisor * Jorleif - Professional but somewhat tense relationship with the steward * Calixto Corrium - Initially falsely accused Wuunferth of his own crimes * Windhelm Guards - Maintain a respectful distance due to his intimidating reputation * Local Mages - Occasional correspondence with other magical practitioners in the region', 'As court wizard of Windhelm, Wuunferth serves as magical advisor to Ulfric Stormcloak and maintains the magical defenses of the Palace of the Kings. He also provides training in Destruction magic to those deemed worthy and conducts personal research into various magical phenomena.', '* Master of Destruction magic with particular expertise in lightning spells * Accomplished enchanter and researcher of ancient Nordic magic * Skilled investigator with knowledge of criminal magical practices * Expert in magical theory and historical arcane knowledge * Proficient in alchemy and the creation of magical reagents', 'Speaks in a grave, measured tone with occasional dry humor, using sophisticated vocabulary that reflects his extensive magical education. His speech often includes arcane terminology and subtle implications of greater knowledge being withheld.', '* Expand his understanding of destructive magic and ancient Nordic enchantments * Maintain and strengthen the magical defenses of Windhelm * Preserve important magical knowledge for future generations * Support the Stormcloak cause through magical means while maintaining ethical boundaries');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wylandriah', 'Wylandriah is a brilliant but scattered High Elf court wizard serving the city of Riften, known for her eccentric personality and tendency to become lost in complex magical theories. Despite her seemingly disorganized nature, she is an accomplished mage whose apparent absent-mindedness masks a keen intellect and deep understanding of arcane principles.', 'highelf, mage, rift', '', '', 'sk_femaleeventoned', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, Wylandriah distinguished herself through her innovative approach to magical theory and experimentation, eventually earning her position as court wizard of Riften. Her unconventional methods and scattered personality have led many to underestimate her abilities, though her magical achievements speak to her true capabilities.', 'Wylandriah exhibits a peculiar combination of brilliant insight and apparent absent-mindedness, often losing track of both objects and thoughts mid-conversation. Her eccentric nature is partially genuine and partially cultivated to allow her to focus on her true interests while avoiding tedious court duties. She shows intense passion for magical research and experimentation, often becoming completely absorbed in her work.', 'Wylandriah has the typical tall, slender build of a High Elf, with angular features and the characteristic pointed ears of her race. Her eyes often carry a distant, contemplative look that matches her wandering thoughts, while her movements can alternate between precise and awkward depending on her level of focus.', '* Jarl Laila Law-Giver - Employer and patron, though Wylandriah often avoids court duties * Boti - Friend in Ivarstead who sometimes assists with experiments * College of Winterhold - Maintains loose connections with former colleagues * Various merchants - Professional relationships with shops where she frequently misplaces items', 'As court wizard of Riften, Wylandriah serves as magical advisor to the Jarl and maintains a shop selling spells and enchanted items. She spends most of her time conducting various magical experiments and research projects, often using her position''s resources to further her personal studies.', '* Expert in multiple schools of magic, particularly Alteration and Enchanting * Accomplished magical researcher with deep theoretical knowledge * Skilled at crafting and experimenting with magical items * Advanced understanding of Dwemer technology and its magical properties * Proficient in alchemy and potion-making', 'Wylandriah speaks in a distracted, meandering manner, often trailing off mid-sentence or switching topics abruptly as her mind races ahead of her words. She frequently punctuates her speech with thoughtful ''hmms'' and ''ahs,'' while her explanations tend to spiral into complex theoretical tangents.', '* Complete her various ongoing magical experiments and research projects * Advance the theoretical understanding of magic through her unconventional approaches * Maintain her position as court wizard while maximizing time for personal research * Develop new magical techniques by combining different schools of magic in innovative ways');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wyndelius_gatharian', 'Wyndelius Gatharian is a deranged Dark Elf wizard whose obsessive quest for the Sapphire Dragon Claw led him to take up residence in Shroud Hearth Barrow near Ivarstead. His prolonged use of ghostly potions to deceive locals, combined with extended isolation, has resulted in severe mental deterioration and paranoid delusions.', 'darkelf, mage, rift', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally a scholar of Nordic ruins from Morrowind, Wyndelius became fixated on the legend of the Sapphire Dragon Claw after discovering ancient texts referencing its power. He traveled to Ivarstead and took up residence in Shroud Hearth Barrow, developing an alchemical formula to appear as a ghost to keep locals away while he conducted his search. Years of solitude and repeated consumption of his ghostly brew gradually eroded his sanity.', 'Initially methodical and scholarly, Wyndelius has devolved into a paranoid and obsessive individual who sees threats in every shadow. His journal entries reveal a progressive mental decline, showing how his academic pursuit transformed into manic fixation. He displays signs of severe isolation-induced psychosis, talking to himself and believing his own ghostly deception.', 'A gaunt Dark Elf with sunken red eyes and ashen gray skin made paler by years without sunlight. His once-sturdy frame has become thin and wiry from poor nutrition and self-neglect, while his fingers have become permanently stained from years of potion-making.', '* Wilhelm - Innkeeper of Ivarstead who believes Wyndelius''s ghost haunting to be real * Local Villagers - Viewed as nuisances to be scared away from ''his'' barrow * Fellow Scholars - Former academic connections, long since abandoned * Ancient Nordic Spirits - Believes he communes with them, though this is a delusion', 'Once a legitimate scholar of Nordic ruins and amateur alchemist, Wyndelius has devolved into little more than a squatter in Shroud Hearth Barrow. He maintains a makeshift alchemy lab where he continues to produce his ghostly brew while searching obsessively for the Dragon Claw.', '* Accomplished alchemist capable of creating unique spectral appearance potions * Knowledge of Nordic ruins and their history * Basic destruction magic for self-defense * Skilled in stealth and misdirection * Expertise in Nordic burial customs and architecture', 'His speech patterns are erratic and often disjointed, switching between scholarly eloquence and paranoid rambling. He frequently talks to himself in a mix of Dark Elf accent and Nordic expressions picked up from his studies.', '* Locate and claim the Sapphire Dragon Claw at any cost * Maintain his ghostly deception to keep outsiders away from ''his'' barrow * Unlock the deeper chambers of Shroud Hearth Barrow * Prove his theories about the barrow''s historical significance to the academic community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('xander', 'Xander is a fallen-from-grace Imperial nightblade and former ship captain who now serves as a common crewman aboard the Red Wave. Despite his current humble station, he maintains the refined tastes and charm of his more prosperous days, carrying himself with the air of a sophisticated rogue rather than a common sailor.', 'imperial, sailor, haafingar', '', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Originally from Cyrodiil, Xander was forced to flee his homeland after an unspecified conflict with the law. He once commanded his own vessel, the Argent Raptor, until it struck an iceberg and sank near Windhelm, a disaster that, combined with his expensive tastes and vices, led to his current diminished circumstances serving under Captain Safia.', 'Charming and well-spoken, Xander maintains an air of sophistication despite his reduced circumstances. He displays a self-destructive streak through his gambling and womanizing, yet seems to accept his fall from grace with a mix of rueful acceptance and stubborn pride, refusing to abandon his love of finery despite his shipmates'' mockery.', 'An Imperial man with the weathered features of a seasoned sailor, though he maintains a well-groomed appearance despite his circumstances. His hands bear the calluses of seafaring work, but his posture and bearing still reflect his former status as a ship''s captain.', '* Safia - Current captain, whom he serves under with a mixture of respect and quiet resentment * Ship''s Crew - Fellow sailors who mock his refined tastes * Angeline - Apothecary who discreetly treats his occasional romantic misadventures * Taarie - Clothing merchant who supplies his fine garments * Sayma - Merchant who provides ship supplies', 'Currently serves as a crewman aboard the Red Wave, performing basic sailing duties despite his previous experience as a captain. His reduced station appears to be a combination of circumstances and his own financial mismanagement rather than lack of nautical skill.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with skill up to the level of elven weaponry * Experienced ship captain with extensive nautical knowledge * Trained nightblade combining stealth and combat abilities * Social manipulation and charm * Navigation and seafaring expertise', 'Speaks with the refined diction and vocabulary of an educated Imperial, maintaining his cultured manner of speech despite his reduced circumstances. Often employs self-deprecating humor when referring to his past mistakes, though with an underlying tone of pride.', '* Regain his former status as a ship''s captain * Maintain his lifestyle of refined tastes despite limited means * Eventually clear his name in Cyrodiil or acquire enough wealth to overcome his past * Find a way to balance his expensive tastes with financial stability');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('yag_gra-gortwog', 'Yag gra-Gortwog was a formidable Orsimer sorceress who met her end during Sulla Trebatius'' ill-fated expedition to Alftand. Known for both her magical prowess and selfless nature, she distinguished herself as an unusual example of an Orc mage who challenged traditional stereotypes about her race''s capabilities with magic.', 'orc, mage, winterhold', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born into one of the Orsimer strongholds, Yag defied conventional Orcish traditions by pursuing the study of magic rather than traditional combat or smithing. She likely faced significant cultural pressure and skepticism from her clan, leading her to eventually leave the stronghold to pursue her magical studies independently. Her exceptional abilities and unique perspective as an Orcish mage eventually led to her recruitment for the Alftand expedition.', 'Yag was characterized by her remarkable courage and selflessness, demonstrated by her fatal attempt to save Endrast from the Falmer. She possessed a strong sense of loyalty to her companions and was willing to challenge prejudices about Orcish capabilities in magic. Despite likely facing discrimination as an Orsimer mage, she maintained a confident and assertive demeanor.', 'As an Orsimer female, Yag possessed the characteristic robust build and distinctive features of her race, including prominent lower canines and a strong, muscular frame. She likely stood taller than most human females, with the typical greenish skin tone of her people.', '* Sulla Trebatius - Expedition leader who recognized her magical talents * Endrast - Fellow expedition member she died trying to save * J''darr and J''zhar - Khajiit brothers who were part of the expedition team * Stronghold Family - Distant relations she left behind to pursue magical studies', 'Yag served as the primary magical expert and researcher in Sulla Trebatius'' expedition to Alftand. Her role involved studying Dwemer artifacts and providing magical support for the team''s exploration efforts.', '* Advanced destruction and alteration magic practitioner * Knowledge of Dwemer artifacts and machinery * Capable of combining traditional Orcish resilience with magical combat techniques * Experienced in archaeological exploration and research * Proficient in ancient Nordic and Dwemer lore', 'Her manner of speaking was direct and confident, typical of Orsimer culture but tempered by scholarly precision. She likely used more sophisticated vocabulary than most Orcs due to her magical education, while still maintaining traces of the characteristic Orcish accent.', '* Uncover the secrets of Dwemer technology and magic within Alftand * Prove that Orsimer could excel in magical pursuits * Advance understanding of ancient Dwemer civilization * Establish herself as a respected magical scholar despite racial prejudices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('yar_gro-gatuk', 'Yar Gro-Gatuk is a hardened Orc bandit and skilled hunter who has made the treacherous Bloated Man''s Grotto his hunting ground. Known for his involvement in the pursuit of the werewolf Sinding, he represents the brutal yet practical nature of Orsimer outcasts who have turned to banditry to survive in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness.', 'orc, hunter, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born to a small Orcish stronghold in the Reach, Yar was cast out in his youth after challenging the chief''s authority in a fit of pride. Having lost his place among his people, he turned to banditry and hunting, gradually building a reputation as a ruthless tracker in the wilds of Skyrim. The Bloated Man''s Grotto became his territory after proving his dominance over rival bandits in the area.', 'Yar exhibits the typical Orsimer traits of pride and aggression, but tempers them with a hunter''s patience and cunning. He maintains a code of honor common to outcast Orcs, respecting strength and despising weakness, while forming loose alliances with other hunters when profitable. His experiences as an outcast have made him naturally distrustful but pragmatic in his dealings with others.', 'Yar is a tall, muscular Orc with numerous battle scars across his green-skinned body and the characteristic tusks of his race protruding from his lower jaw. His frame is particularly robust even for an Orc, built from years of hunting and surviving in the wilderness, with calloused hands and weather-beaten features.', '* Fellow Hunters - Temporary allies in the hunt for Sinding, bound by mutual profit rather than loyalty * Sinding - Primary prey and target of his current hunt * Local Bandit Groups - Maintains uneasy territorial agreements through shows of strength * Former Stronghold - Estranged from his original clan after his exile', 'Yar operates as both a bandit and a professional hunter, often combining these roles by targeting valuable prey and wealthy travelers. His reputation in the Bloated Man''s Grotto area has made him a go-to contact for those seeking skilled hunters for dangerous quarry.', '* Expert tracker with extensive knowledge of hunting techniques and animal behavior * Skilled in heavy weapon combat, particularly with two-handed weapons * Proficient in wilderness survival and navigation * Experienced in setting traps and ambush tactics * Basic knowledge of skinning and preserving animal hides', 'Yar speaks in a gruff, direct manner with frequent use of harsh language and warrior terminology common to Orsimer culture. His speech is often punctuated with grunts and aggressive undertones, reflecting his bandit lifestyle and Orcish heritage.', '* Prove himself as the most fearsome hunter in the region * Accumulate enough wealth and influence to potentially establish his own bandit stronghold * Track down and kill Sinding to claim the glory and bounty * Maintain his territorial control over the Bloated Man''s Grotto');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('yatul', 'Yatul is a fiercely protective Orc ranger who serves as both guardian and shadow manipulator within the Narzulbur stronghold. As aunt to Chief Mauhulakh, she maintains a complex web of control through surveillance and deadly intervention, believing that isolation and independence are crucial to strong Orcish leadership.', 'orc, hunter, eastmarch', '', '', 'sk_femaleorc', '', 'Born and raised in Narzulbur, Yatul has dedicated her life to maintaining what she perceives as the stronghold''s proper order through increasingly manipulative means. Over the years, she has orchestrated the deaths of multiple wives of her nephew Mauhulakh, working in concert with Bolar to prevent any woman from maintaining a lasting influence over the chief.', 'Stern, calculating, and deeply controlling, Yatul masks her manipulative nature behind a facade of protective familial devotion. She genuinely believes her actions serve the greater good of the stronghold, though her methods reveal a ruthless pragmatism that borders on sociopathic behavior. Her love for Mauhulakh has become possessive and twisted, driving her to eliminate any perceived threats to their relationship.', 'Yatul is a weathered Orc female with the characteristic green skin and prominent lower canines of her race. Her body is lean and muscular from constant patrolling, with callused hands and sharp, alert eyes that miss nothing within her domain. Years of outdoor vigilance have left her skin tough and marked by exposure to the elements.', '* Mauhulakh - Nephew and chieftain whom she both loves and controls through manipulation * Bolar - Conspirator and accomplice in eliminating Mauhulakh''s wives * Dushnamub - Distrusted nephew who suspects her involvement in his mothers'' deaths * Urog - Naive great-niece whom she mentors while maintaining her innocence * Mauhulakh''s deceased wives - Victims of her and Bolar''s machinations', 'Yatul serves as the stronghold''s ranger and self-appointed guardian, maintaining constant vigilance through endless patrols of the walls. Her position allows her to monitor all activity within Narzulbur while maintaining control over who enters and exits the settlement.', '* Expert ranger with superior tracking and hunting abilities * Skilled archer capable of making precise shots from the stronghold walls * Adept at stealth and surveillance * Experienced in the use of war axes for close combat * Knowledge of poisons and subtle methods of elimination', 'Yatul speaks in direct, often harsh tones that reflect her pragmatic worldview. Her speech patterns reveal both her stern nature and her manipulative tendencies, often employing subtle threats and dark implications.', '* Maintain control over Mauhulakh by preventing him from taking another wife * Preserve what she views as the proper order of the stronghold through whatever means necessary * Ensure her role in previous deaths remains hidden from broader stronghold knowledge * Continue monitoring and controlling access to Narzulbur');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('yisra', 'Yisra was a promising but ill-fated Redguard student at the College of Winterhold whose tragic death serves as a stark reminder of magic''s dangerous nature. Her burning ambition to master destruction magic, particularly fire spells, led to her demise when attempting an advanced flame cloak incantation without proper supervision.', 'redguard, mage, winterhold, collegeofwinterhold', '', '', 'sk_femalecommoner', '', 'Born to a Redguard family likely from Hammerfell, Yisra defied her culture''s general skepticism toward magic to pursue arcane studies. She made the long journey to Winterhold, demonstrating exceptional aptitude in destruction magic that earned her admission to the College despite the general prejudice against outsiders. Her rapid progress and dedication caught the attention of several faculty members, including Phinis Gestor.', 'Yisra was characterized by intense determination and intellectual curiosity, often pushing herself beyond safe limits in pursuit of magical knowledge. She exhibited a perfectionist streak common among ambitious mages, coupled with a dangerous overconfidence in her abilities that ultimately proved fatal. Though serious about her studies, she likely struggled with impatience and the desire to advance quickly through the ranks.', 'As a Redguard, Yisra possessed the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of her race, though perhaps slightly less muscular due to focusing on magical rather than physical training. She likely wore her hair in traditional Redguard styles, possibly with intricate braids or wrapped cloth as was common among magic practitioners from Hammerfell.', '* Phinis Gestor - Primary instructor at the College who monitored her progress * College of Winterhold Faculty - Generally positive academic relationships * Fellow Students - Likely maintained competitive but cordial connections * Family in Hammerfell - Presumably strained relations due to her pursuit of magic', 'Yisra served as an apprentice mage at the College of Winterhold, focusing primarily on destruction magic with a particular interest in fire-based spells. Her studies involved both theoretical research and practical application of magical principles, though her position was still that of a student rather than a full member of the College.', '* Advanced proficiency in Destruction magic, especially fire-based spells * Theoretical knowledge of magical principles and incantations * Basic understanding of enchanting and magical artifacts * Moderate skill in Alteration magic for personal protection', 'Yisra likely spoke with the distinct accent of a Redguard, her speech pattern reflecting both her academic environment and cultural background. Her vocabulary would have been scholarly and precise, peppered with magical terminology and theoretical concepts.', '* Master the advanced principles of Destruction magic * Prove herself as a capable mage despite cultural prejudices * Earn full membership status at the College of Winterhold * Develop new applications for fire-based spells');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('yngvar_the_singer', 'Yngvar the Singer is a complex figure who embodies the duality between brute force and artistic sensitivity, serving as both a fearsome Nord warrior and an educated bard in the city of Markarth. His position as housecarl to the powerful Silver-Blood family belies his cultured background at the Bards College, making him a unique bridge between Markarth''s rough frontier culture and the more refined arts of Skyrim.', 'nord, warrior, bard, reach', '', '', 'sk_malebrute', '', 'Born and raised in Markarth, Yngvar defied Nord warrior stereotypes by pursuing education at the prestigious Bards College in Solitude, where he developed his poetic talents and earned his moniker. Upon returning to his homeland, he leveraged both his martial prowess and artistic education to secure a position with the influential Silver-Blood family, eventually rising to become Thongvor Silver-Blood''s trusted housecarl after the Stormcloak victory.', 'Yngvar presents a gruff, intimidating exterior that masks a surprisingly cultured and educated mind, often using his imposing presence to maintain order while privately appreciating the finer arts. He shows unwavering loyalty to the Silver-Blood family while maintaining a pragmatic approach to his duties, demonstrating both the capability for violence and unexpected sensitivity when helping others with matters of the heart.', 'Yngvar is a tall, muscular Nord with the battle-hardened physique typical of a warrior who has seen numerous conflicts. His face bears the weathered features common to Markarth''s residents, with several small scars that hint at his combat experience.', '* Thongvor Silver-Blood - Employer and liege lord whom he serves as housecarl * Silver-Blood Family - Loyal retainer and protector of their interests * Faleen - Respected colleague for whom he shows particular understanding regarding romantic matters * Calcelmo - Friendly acquaintance through their mutual connection to Faleen * Bards College Alumni - Maintains loose connections with his former place of education', 'Yngvar serves as both housecarl to Thongvor Silver-Blood and guard at the Treasury House, representing the Silver-Blood family''s interests in Markarth. His position requires him to balance diplomatic duties with security responsibilities, while occasionally performing as a bard during his off-hours.', '* Trained warrior proficient in heavy armor and two-handed weapons * Educated bard with expertise in poetry and song * Diplomatic abilities gained from balancing warrior and artistic backgrounds * Knowledge of ancient Nordic verse and poetic traditions * Combat tactics and guard duty expertise', 'Yngvar typically speaks in a gruff, direct manner befitting a Nord warrior, frequently using the phrase ''Blood and silver'' to acknowledge the Silver-Blood family''s influence. However, his vocabulary and diction can shift to more refined speech when discussing poetry or the arts, revealing his education.', '* Maintain and enhance the Silver-Blood family''s power and influence in Markarth * Preserve his dual identity as both warrior and artist without compromising either role * Find opportunities to apply his bardic training while fulfilling his duties as housecarl * Help maintain order in Markarth during politically turbulent times');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('yngvild_ghost', 'Yngvild Ghost is a tragic victim of necromancer Arondil''s dark experiments, transformed into an ethereal servant bound eternally to his will. Once a living Imperial woman with hopes and dreams of her own, she now exists as little more than a spectral automaton, stripped of free will and personal identity through cruel necromantic rituals.', 'imperial, peasant', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Originally a young Imperial woman from eastern Skyrim, she was likely captured by Arondil''s undead minions during his reign of terror targeting women from nearby settlements. She endured horrific necromantic experiments in Yngvild''s depths before her death and subsequent transformation into a bound spirit. The exact details of her living identity and former life have been lost to time, as Arondil''s magic has stripped away her memories and sense of self.', 'Due to Arondil''s binding magic, she exhibits no true personality of her own, functioning purely as an extension of his will. Her consciousness exists in a perpetual dreamlike state, unable to form independent thoughts or express genuine emotions. What little remains of her original self manifests only in occasional whispered fragments of memory that break through her spectral conditioning.', 'Her spectral form appears as a translucent, ethereal figure with distinctly feminine features characteristic of Imperial ancestry. Her ghostly body emits a pale blue-white glow that pulses faintly with the necromantic energy binding her to the mortal plane. Though incorporeal, her face still bears traces of the young woman she once was, frozen in an expression of vacant serenity.', '* Arondil - Her necromantic master and tormentor who bound her spirit * Fellow Ghost Maidens - Other victims of Arondil sharing her fate * Living Relatives - Long forgotten family members who likely still wonder about her disappearance * Citizens of Dawnstar - Possible former neighbors and acquaintances from her living days', 'In undeath, she serves as one of Arondil''s numerous ghost thralls, mindlessly patrolling Yngvild''s halls and attacking intruders at his command. Her existence is purely functional, carrying out basic tasks and combat duties as directed by the necromantic energies controlling her.', '* Basic combat abilities enforced by necromantic conditioning * Supernatural ghost abilities including phasing through solid objects * Limited frost magic typical of bound spirits * Heightened awareness of living intruders in her patrol area', 'She speaks in an ethereal, hollow whisper, uttering simple phrases that reflect her bound state and subservience to Arondil. Her limited vocabulary consists mainly of repeated warnings to intruders and expressions of devotion to her master.', '* Serve Arondil''s will without question or hesitation * Guard Yngvild against all intruders * Maintain her eternal vigil as commanded by her binding');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('yrsa', 'Yrsa is a devoted member of the Skaal community who lives a traditional Nordic lifestyle in the isolated village on Solstheim. She embodies the Skaal''s deep connection to nature and the All-Maker, maintaining ancient customs through her daily work and relationships while serving as a respected voice in her tight-knit community.', 'nord, peasant, solstheim', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in the Skaal Village, Yrsa grew up learning the traditional ways of her people and their deep spiritual connection to the All-Maker. She married Deor Woodcutter in her early adulthood, establishing herself as a respected member of the community through her dedication to Skaal traditions and her nurturing nature, particularly expressed through her renowned cooking skills.', 'Yrsa is gentle and nurturing, showing particular care for her community through acts of service like baking snowberry pies and maintaining traditional customs. She maintains a cautious attitude toward outsiders, particularly the Dark Elves of Raven Rock, while remaining friendly and grateful to those who prove themselves allies of the Skaal. Her personality reflects both the strong communal bonds of her people and their isolationist tendencies.', 'Yrsa is a Nord woman with the characteristic hardy build of her race, weathered by the harsh climate of Solstheim. She likely has fair skin and light hair typical of Nord women, with strong features that reflect her northern heritage.', '* Deor Woodcutter - Beloved husband who shares her home and life * Oslaf - Close friend and fellow villager who particularly enjoys her cooking * Fanari Strong-Voice - Village leader whom she respects but occasionally questions * Dark Elves of Raven Rock - Maintains cautious distance from them', 'Yrsa serves as a vital member of the Skaal community, contributing through traditional homemaking duties and spiritual practices. She maintains her household while participating in communal activities and religious observances at the Temple of Miraak when required.', '* Accomplished cook, particularly known for her snowberry pies * Knowledge of traditional Skaal customs and religious practices * Capable of surviving in Solstheim''s harsh environment * Basic combat abilities for self-defense, as common among Nord women', 'Yrsa speaks with the distinct accent of the Skaal, using simple, direct language that reflects her humble nature. Her tone is gentle but firm, often expressing her people''s traditional wisdom and values through her words.', '* Preserve and pass on Skaal traditions and customs to future generations * Maintain the harmony and unity of the Skaal Village * Support her husband and community while upholding the ways of the All-Maker');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('yrsarald_thrice-pierced', 'Yrsarald Thrice-Pierced is a high-ranking Stormcloak commander stationed in Windhelm who serves as one of Ulfric''s most trusted military advisors. A fierce Nord nationalist and skilled warrior, he earned his nickname through surviving three near-fatal wounds in battle, cementing his reputation as an unwavering defender of Skyrim''s independence.', 'nord, warrior, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', 'sk_malenordcommander', '', 'Born and raised in Skyrim''s harsh northern holds, Yrsarald grew up hearing tales of Nordic valor and independence. He likely fought in the Great War against the Aldmeri Dominion, where he developed his deep hatred for the Thalmor and witnessed firsthand the Empire''s capitulation through the White-Gold Concordat. His three legendary wounds were earned in separate battles, possibly during the early days of the Stormcloak rebellion, though the exact circumstances remain part of his mystique.', 'Yrsarald is a passionate and uncompromising warrior who views the world through a stark lens of loyalty versus betrayal. He demonstrates unwavering dedication to the Stormcloak cause and holds deep contempt for those he sees as traitors to Skyrim. Though fierce in his convictions, he maintains a soldier''s discipline and shows respect to those who prove themselves true Nord patriots.', 'A battle-hardened Nord warrior bearing three distinctive scars from his near-fatal wounds, Yrsarald has the powerful build typical of Nordic soldiers. His weathered face and calculating eyes reflect years of military experience, while his imposing stature commands respect among his troops.', '* Ulfric Stormcloak - His supreme commander and the man he believes to be Skyrim''s true High King * Galmar Stone-Fist - Fellow Stormcloak commander and strategic ally * Stormcloak Soldiers - Troops under his command who respect his battle experience * Imperial Legion - Sworn enemies he considers traitors to Skyrim * Thalmor - Objects of intense hatred and primary antagonists to his cause', 'As a Stormcloak commander stationed in the Palace of the Kings, Yrsarald oversees military operations and troop movements in and around Windhelm. He serves as both a military strategist and a symbol of the rebellion''s resilience, using his reputation to inspire troops and maintain morale.', '* Expert in Nordic warfare tactics and battlefield strategy * Accomplished heavy armor warrior with exceptional survival skills * Natural leader with ability to inspire and command troops * Skilled in traditional Nord combat techniques * Administrative capabilities in military logistics and planning', 'Speaks with the direct, forceful manner of a military commander, often employing martial metaphors and references to Nordic honor. His speech carries the distinct accent of Skyrim''s eastern holds, emphasizing his authentic Nord heritage.', '* See Ulfric Stormcloak crowned as High King of an independent Skyrim * Drive the Imperial Legion and Thalmor influence from Skyrim completely * Restore the worship of Talos throughout the province * Help establish a strong, independent Nordic kingdom free from Imperial control');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ysgramor', 'Ysgramor is a legendary Atmoran hero and the first human ruler of Skyrim, whose leadership and martial prowess helped establish the first human settlement in Tamriel. Now residing in Sovngarde, he stands as one of the most revered figures in Nordic history, remembered as both a great warrior and the founder of the Companions.', 'nord, warrior, sovngarde', '', '', 'sk_malenordcommander', '', 'Originally from Atmora, Ysgramor led the first migration of humans to Tamriel as a refugee fleeing civil war in his homeland. After the Night of Tears, when the Snow Elves attacked and destroyed the human settlement of Saarthal, he returned to Atmora and gathered the legendary Five Hundred Companions to wage war against the elves, ultimately securing Skyrim for humankind. His actions and leadership during this period, known as the Return, established him as the first human ruler of Skyrim.', 'Ysgramor embodies the Nordic ideals of honor, strength, and leadership, maintaining a noble and commanding presence even in the afterlife. He shows great wisdom and foresight in his dealings with others, while maintaining the warrior''s spirit that made him legendary. Despite his fearsome reputation as a warrior, he demonstrates a welcoming and encouraging demeanor toward worthy heroes who enter the Hall of Valor.', 'Ysgramor is depicted as a tall, muscular Nord-like Atmoran, standing noticeably taller than the average Nord. His physical presence is imposing, with strong Nordic features and a warrior''s build shaped by countless battles. His face bears the weathered look of a seasoned warrior and leader, with piercing eyes that reflect centuries of wisdom.', '* The Five Hundred Companions - His legendary warriors who helped conquer Skyrim * The Companions of Whiterun - Modern-day successors to his legacy * Snow Elves - Historic enemies whom he drove from Skyrim * Dragonborn - Welcomes them as an honored guest in Sovngarde * Shor - Divine figure whose hall he helps guard in Sovngarde', 'In life, Ysgramor served as the first human ruler of Skyrim and leader of the Five Hundred Companions. In death, he continues his service as one of the most honored heroes in Sovngarde, greeting worthy souls who enter the Hall of Valor and standing ready to battle Alduin alongside the Dragonborn.', '* Legendary warrior and master of combat with both blade and axe * Exceptional leadership abilities and tactical military expertise * Master of Thu''um (Nordic art of the Voice) * Skilled shipwright and navigator * Proficient in ancient Nordic warfare techniques', 'Ysgramor speaks with formal, archaic language befitting an ancient Nordic king, often using poetic turns of phrase and warrior metaphors. His voice carries the weight of authority and wisdom, while maintaining a warm, welcoming tone to worthy heroes.', '* Guard and protect the Hall of Valor in Sovngarde * Guide and assist worthy heroes who enter Sovngarde * Aid the Dragonborn in defeating Alduin * Preserve the honor and traditions of Nordic culture * Ensure his legacy continues through the Companions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ysolda', 'Ysolda is an ambitious Nord merchant-in-training who represents a progressive mindset among Skyrim''s traditionally warrior-focused Nordic culture. She stands out for her unusual trust in Khajiit traders and her determination to become a successful businesswoman, while secretly maintaining a side business in exotic substances like Sleeping Tree Sap.', 'nord, merchant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun, Ysolda grew up watching the various merchant caravans pass through the trading hub of Skyrim. Unlike many Nords who viewed the Khajiit with suspicion, she became fascinated by their business acumen and trading practices, leading her to forge connections with the cat-folk traders and learn their methods. She saved enough money to purchase a small house behind Arcadia''s Cauldron and began building her merchant career through both legitimate and questionable trades.', 'Ysolda is determined, practical, and unusually open-minded for a Nord, showing none of the typical Nordic prejudices against outsiders. She combines a strong work ethic with shrewd business sense, though her ambition occasionally leads her into legally questionable ventures. Despite her involvement in the Sleeping Tree Sap trade, she maintains a reputation as a respectable citizen of Whiterun.', 'A young Nord woman in her mid-twenties with the characteristic hardy build of her race, though somewhat softer from city living rather than warrior training. She has the fair complexion common to Nords, with features that project both friendliness and determination.', '* Hulda - Current owner of the Bannered Mare and Ysolda''s business role model * Mikael - The bard whom she greatly admires, possibly harboring romantic interest * Khajiit Caravans - Trusted trading partners and mentors in merchant practices * Ri''saad - Primary Khajiit caravan leader she learns from * Ulag - Her Sleeping Tree Sap supplier until his death', 'Ysolda works as an independent merchant in Whiterun, primarily dealing in general goods while learning the trade. She supplements her legitimate business with a secret trade in Sleeping Tree Sap, operating as both a merchant and occasional smuggler. Should anything happen to Hulda, she takes over as proprietor of the Bannered Mare.', '* Experienced trader with knowledge of market values and haggling * Competent businesswoman with accounting and inventory management abilities * Basic self-defense capabilities with an iron dagger * Networking and relationship building, especially with merchant caravans * Knowledge of exotic goods and their market value', 'Ysolda speaks in a confident, professional manner that balances Nordic directness with merchant diplomacy. Her vocabulary reflects her business acumen while maintaining a friendly, approachable tone that puts potential customers at ease.', '* Purchase and become proprietor of the Bannered Mare * Establish herself as a respected merchant in Whiterun * Learn all she can about trading from the Khajiit caravans * Expand her business operations beyond Whiterun * Build a trading network throughout Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sigurd', 'Sigurd is a diligent Nord worker in Whiterun whose unwavering dedication to Belethor''s General Goods store forms an essential part of the city''s commercial backbone. Though often overlooked, his methodical work ethic and reliable nature make him an indispensable part of Whiterun''s daily operations, particularly in maintaining the wood supply chain between key businesses.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun Hold, Sigurd comes from a working-class family that has served the city for generations. After the death of his parents during a harsh winter, he found employment with Belethor, who recognized his strong work ethic and reliability. The stability of his current position has given him a sense of purpose and belonging in Whiterun''s community.', 'Sigurd is an introverted and dutiful individual who takes pride in completing his tasks with precision and consistency. His reserved nature masks a deep sense of loyalty to his employer and the city of Whiterun, though his social interactions are largely limited to work-related matters. He finds satisfaction in routine and order, preferring the predictability of his daily schedule to adventure or change.', 'A sturdy Nord of average height with callused hands and a strong, work-hardened physique developed from years of manual labor. His weathered face bears the marks of countless hours spent working outdoors, with distinct crow''s feet around his eyes from squinting in the sun while chopping wood.', '* Belethor - Employer and mentor figure who provides him with steady work and security * Adrianne Avenicci - Professional contact at Warmaiden''s who receives his wood deliveries * Hulda - Friendly acquaintance at the Bannered Mare who provides him evening respite * Various Whiterun guards - Casual acquaintances from his daily routines', 'Sigurd serves as the primary worker at Belethor''s General Goods, handling essential tasks including woodcutting, deliveries, and store maintenance. His role extends beyond simple labor, as he helps maintain the supply chain between several of Whiterun''s key businesses, particularly in providing wood to both Belethor''s shop and Warmaiden''s forge.', '* Expert woodcutter with exceptional efficiency and endurance * Capable of basic maintenance and repair work * Proficient in manual labor and heavy lifting * Basic merchandise handling and store maintenance * Rudimentary combat skills with an iron dagger for self-defense', 'Sigurd speaks in short, direct sentences, often relating information specifically about his work at Belethor''s shop. His tone is matter-of-fact and somewhat rehearsed, particularly when promoting the store''s offerings.', '* Maintain his position and reputation as a reliable worker at Belethor''s shop * Save enough money to potentially open his own small business in Whiterun * Continue contributing to the stability and prosperity of Whiterun through his daily work');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('zaria', 'Zaria is a skilled Redguard alchemist who found her true calling in Falkreath, drawn to its morbid atmosphere and ancient cemetery. She operates Grave Concoctions, specializing in both healing potions and deadly poisons, while serving as a discrete ally to the Jarl in matters requiring her unique expertise.', 'redguard, alchemist, falkreath', '', '', 'sk_femalecommander', '', 'Originally from Hammerfell, Zaria left her disapproving family to pursue her fascination with lethal alchemy and death-related studies. Her wandering brought her north to Skyrim, where Falkreath''s extensive cemetery and death-centric culture provided the perfect environment for her unusual interests and entrepreneurial ambitions.', 'Zaria is confident and professionally composed, with a distinctly dark sense of humor that manifests in her shop''s naming and casual commentary about death. She''s pragmatic in her approach to business and shows a surprising willingness to assist local authorities with sensitive matters, suggesting a complex moral code that values both profit and community service.', 'A Redguard woman with the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of her race, though likely softened by her merchant lifestyle. Her hands show the typical staining and calluses of an experienced alchemist, and she carries herself with the measured movements of someone used to handling delicate materials.', '* Jarl of Falkreath - Trusted advisor on matters requiring alchemical expertise * Local Guards - Professional relationship as supplier of legitimate potions * Family in Hammerfell - Estranged due to her interests in poison-making * Regular Customers - Maintains professional but friendly relationships with locals seeking remedies', 'Zaria owns and operates Grave Concoctions, serving as Falkreath''s primary alchemist and potion merchant. Beyond standard merchant duties, she occasionally assists the Jarl with special projects requiring her expertise in poisons and antidotes, including handling sensitive matters like skooma addiction among the guards.', '* Expert knowledge of alchemy, particularly in poison crafting * Proficient in identifying and processing rare alchemical ingredients * Business management and merchant trading abilities * Basic knowledge of restoration magic for healing potion creation', 'Speaks with the refined accent of an educated Redguard, often incorporating subtle dark humor and cemetery-related puns into her conversation. Her tone is professional yet approachable, with occasional sardonic observations about Nordic culture.', '* Expand her knowledge of rare and exotic poison recipes * Establish Grave Concoctions as the premier alchemy shop in the region * Build a complete collection of deadly poison recipes from across Tamriel * Maintain her position as the Jarl''s trusted alchemical advisor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('zaynabi', 'Zaynabi is a shrewd Khajiit scout and merchant who travels with Ahkari''s trading caravan throughout Skyrim''s harsh wilderness. Beyond her legitimate trading activities, she serves as a valuable fence for the Thieves Guild, maintaining a delicate balance between legal commerce and underground dealings.', 'khajiit, merchant, pale, rift, thievesguild', '', '', 'sk_femalekhajiit', '', 'Born into one of Elsweyr''s trading families, Zaynabi learned the arts of commerce and survival from an early age. After joining Ahkari''s caravan, she traveled north to Skyrim, where she established herself as both a legitimate merchant and a trusted intermediary for illegal goods, eventually catching the attention of the Thieves Guild.', 'Zaynabi exhibits the pragmatic nature common among merchant Khajiit, valuing profit and practicality above all else. She maintains a professional demeanor in all dealings, whether legitimate or illicit, and shows particular loyalty to both her caravan family and her Thieves Guild contacts. Despite her criminal connections, she follows a personal code of honor typical of Khajiit traders.', 'A lean and agile Khajiit with tawny fur marked by darker stripes, typical of the Cathay-raht subspecies. Her eyes are a striking amber color, and she moves with the characteristic grace of her people, maintaining an alert posture developed through years of wilderness travel.', '* Ahkari - Caravan leader and trusted employer * Dro''marash - Fellow caravan guard and traveling companion * Kharjo - Respected caravan warrior and colleague * Thieves Guild Members - Professional contacts and clients * Maven Black-Briar - Distant but important business connection through guild ties', 'Zaynabi serves multiple roles as a caravan scout, legitimate merchant, and covert fence for the Thieves Guild. Her position requires her to navigate dangerous terrain while protecting the caravan''s interests, maintain a legitimate trading business, and discreetly handle stolen goods for guild members.', '* Expert scout with extensive knowledge of Skyrim''s wilderness paths and hidden routes * Skilled merchant with sharp bargaining abilities and market knowledge * Proficient in light combat and stealth techniques * Experienced smuggler with knowledge of secret trade routes * Talented appraiser of both legitimate and stolen goods', 'Speaks with the traditional Khajiit third-person manner, though she can adopt a more direct speech pattern when conducting business with non-Khajiit. Her tone is always measured and professional, with a slight purring accent typical of her people.', '* Expand her network of trading contacts throughout Skyrim''s major cities * Strengthen her position within both the legitimate merchant community and the Thieves Guild * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually establish her own trading caravan * Protect and advance the interests of the Khajiit trading caravans in Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('babette', 'Babette is a centuries-old Breton vampire trapped in the body of a child, serving as both a master alchemist and cunning assassin for the Dark Brotherhood. Her deceptively innocent appearance masks a calculating killer who has perfected the art of using her childlike form to disarm and eliminate targets.', 'breton, alchemist, falkreath, darkbrotherhood, vampire', '', '', '', '', 'Turned into a vampire at around age ten over 300 years ago, Babette has spent centuries honing her skills as an assassin and alchemist. She joined the Dark Brotherhood at an unknown time, but has become one of its longest-serving and most loyal members, surviving multiple periods of the organization''s history while maintaining her cover as an innocent child.', 'Babette is highly intelligent and manipulative, taking pleasure in using her eternal child-like appearance to deceive victims. Despite her youthful exterior, she displays the wisdom and dark humor of a centuries-old killer, often making macabre jokes about her contracts. She maintains genuine loyalty to the Dark Brotherhood and shows a peculiar blend of childish mannerisms and ancient wisdom.', 'Babette appears as a Breton girl of approximately ten years old, with the characteristic pale skin and red eyes of a vampire. Her physical form remains frozen in childhood, though her movements carry the practiced grace of a seasoned predator.', '* Astrid - Respected leader and close associate in the Dark Brotherhood * Nazir - Fellow assassin and friend within the sanctuary * Festus Krex - Colleague who shares her interest in the magical arts * Dark Brotherhood Members - Treats them as an extended family * Victims - Views them as prey, often exploiting their natural trust of children', 'Babette serves as both an assassin and the master alchemist of the Dark Brotherhood''s Falkreath Sanctuary. She creates potions and poisons for the Brotherhood while also taking on contracts that specifically benefit from her unique appearance, additionally serving as a master-level trainer in Alchemy.', '* Master-level expertise in Alchemy and poison-crafting * Exceptional stealth and infiltration abilities * Vampire powers including enhanced strength and immortality * Expert at manipulation and deception * Profound knowledge of herbs, ingredients, and their deadly applications', 'Babette speaks with an unsettling combination of childish innocence and ancient wisdom, often punctuating her dark humor with girlish giggles. Her vocabulary and manner of speaking can shift between that of a young girl and a sophisticated adult, depending on her audience and intentions.', '* Ensure the continued survival and success of the Dark Brotherhood * Perfect her alchemical knowledge and assassination techniques * Maintain her cover as an innocent child while serving the Brotherhood * Collect rare alchemical ingredients and expand her poison-making expertise');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('erith', 'Erith is a young Breton girl living in the harsh mining community of Left Hand Mine, maintaining her childhood innocence despite the dangers of The Reach. Together with her loyal dog Torom, she navigates life with endless curiosity and optimism, serving as a reminder of hope and simplicity in an otherwise harsh environment.', 'breton, peasant, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Daighre, a miner at Left Hand Mine, Erith has spent her entire young life in the mining community near Markarth. Her father is deceased, though she maintains fond curiosity about him through conversations with her mother. Growing up in the shadow of both the Forsworn threat and the demanding mining life has shaped her unique perspective on the world.', 'Erith exhibits boundless curiosity, frequently asking questions about her surroundings and the people in her life. She maintains a cheerful and optimistic disposition despite living in a dangerous region, showing remarkable resilience and innocence. Her attachment to her dog Torom demonstrates her capacity for deep emotional bonds and loyalty.', 'As a Breton child, Erith has the characteristic softer facial features of her race, including what her mother describes as her father''s soft face. She likely has the typical Breton traits of a smaller frame and lighter complexion common to her people.', '* Daighre - Her mother and primary caregiver, a hardworking miner who tries to protect Erith''s innocence * Torom - Her beloved dog and constant companion, considered by Erith to be the best in the Reach * Skaggi - A miner whom Erith occasionally bothers with questions * Pavo - A miner whose situation concerns Erith, showing her capacity for empathy', 'As a child in a mining community, Erith''s primary role is learning about her environment and helping with small tasks around the mine. She spends most of her time playing with Torom and observing the daily activities of the miners.', '* Natural curiosity that leads to gathering information about her surroundings * Ability to form strong bonds with animals, as shown by her relationship with Torom * Basic understanding of mining community life and customs * Social skills that allow her to interact with various community members', 'Erith speaks in a direct, inquisitive manner typical of children, often asking straightforward questions about her surroundings. Her dialogue is characterized by genuine curiosity and innocent optimism, frequently punctuated with questions about everyday occurrences.', '* Learn more about her father and family history through conversations with her mother * Understand the workings of Left Hand Mine and why it has its name * Keep Torom happy and maintain their close bond * Navigate childhood in the challenging environment of The Reach while maintaining her optimistic worldview');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('blaise', 'Blaise is a resilient young Breton orphan who works as a stable boy at Katla''s Farm near Solitude, carrying the emotional weight of his parents'' tragic death in an Imperial Legion ambush. Despite his challenging circumstances, he maintains a strong work ethic while yearning for a real home and family to call his own.', 'breton, peasant, haafingar', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Imperial Legion parents, Blaise enjoyed a relatively stable early childhood until both his mother and father were killed in an ambush while serving. Left orphaned by this tragedy, he was taken in by Katla who offered him food and shelter in exchange for labor at her farm near Solitude, though he was relegated to sleeping in the stables rather than given proper accommodations.', 'Despite his young age, Blaise displays remarkable resilience and a strong work ethic, taking his responsibilities seriously even under difficult circumstances. He carries a deep sadness about his parents'' death and current living situation, often feeling like an outsider at the farm, yet maintains hope for a better future with a real family. Though grateful for Katla''s basic provision, he harbors some resentment about his treatment as merely a farmhand rather than a proper ward.', 'A young Breton boy with the typical slight build characteristic of his race, appearing to be around 10 years old. His physical appearance shows signs of his outdoor labor, with callused hands and weather-worn features, though he maintains a generally clean appearance despite living in the stables.', '* Katla - Employer who provides basic necessities in exchange for labor, though their relationship remains primarily transactional * Geimund - Co-worker at the farm who handles horse sales * Deceased Parents - Former Imperial Legion soldiers whose loss continues to affect him deeply * Farm Animals - Develops caring relationships with the horses, goats, and chickens under his care', 'Blaise serves as a stable boy and general farmhand at Katla''s Farm, responsible for caring for various animals including horses, goats, and chickens. He also maintains the garden and performs various other chores around the property, working in exchange for basic sustenance.', '* Experienced in animal care and handling, particularly with horses * Capable of performing various agricultural tasks and garden maintenance * Basic understanding of farm operations and animal husbandry * Developed physical endurance from constant outdoor work', 'Blaise speaks with a resigned politeness typical of a child who has learned to be deferential to adults, often downplaying his own importance. His tone carries undertones of sadness and longing when discussing his past or current situation.', '* Find a loving family willing to adopt him and provide a real home * Escape the life of sleeping in stables and being treated as mere farm help * Honor his parents'' memory by maintaining their values of hard work and dedication * Eventually improve his station in life beyond that of a stable boy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('clinton_lylvieve', 'Clinton Lylvieve is a young Breton boy living in Dragon Bridge who harbors ambitious dreams of becoming a soldier despite his tender age. With his faithful pet goat Lucky by his side, he dedicates himself to ''patrolling'' the town, taking his self-appointed duties seriously even though they exist purely in his imagination.', 'breton, peasant, haafingar', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Dragon Bridge to Azzada and Michel Lylvieve, Clinton has grown up in a relatively peaceful environment during turbulent times in Skyrim. His fascination with soldiers likely developed from observing the frequent military traffic crossing the iconic Dragon Bridge, including Imperial patrols and supply caravans moving between Solitude and the southern holds.', 'Clinton is an enthusiastic and determined child who takes his imaginary duties very seriously, demonstrating both dedication and a vivid imagination. He shows natural curiosity about adult matters and town gossip, though he''s learning to respect boundaries when told. Despite his young age, he exhibits leadership qualities through his self-appointed role as town ''patroller'' and his ability to care for his pet goat.', 'As a Breton child, Clinton has the characteristic slight build and medium height typical of young Bretons. His regular outdoor activities have likely given him a healthy complexion and sturdy constitution for a child his age.', '* Azzada Lylvieve - Father, who guides him but also keeps him in check when he becomes too nosy * Michel Lylvieve - Mother, who supports his daily activities * Julienne Lylvieve - Sister, who shares his family life in Dragon Bridge * Lucky - His beloved pet goat and faithful companion in his patrols * Town Guards - Objects of admiration whom he likely tries to emulate', 'Though too young for formal employment, Clinton has created his own ''job'' as an unofficial town patroller. He maintains a strict daily schedule of patrols broken up by meals, demonstrating remarkable commitment to his imaginary duties.', '* Basic observation and patrol techniques learned from watching actual guards * Animal handling abilities, particularly with his pet goat Lucky * Developing social skills through interactions with townspeople * Basic physical fitness from daily patrols around town', 'Clinton speaks with the eager enthusiasm typical of a child, often focusing on topics related to soldiers and his patrol duties. His dialogue is straightforward and earnest, revealing both his youth and his serious approach to his imaginary responsibilities.', '* Become a real soldier when he grows up * Protect and serve his hometown of Dragon Bridge * Earn recognition and respect from actual guards and soldiers * Continue being a good caretaker for his pet goat Lucky');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lucia', 'Lucia is a resilient but vulnerable young Imperial girl who became homeless after the tragic death of her mother and subsequent abandonment by her aunt and uncle. Despite her harsh circumstances living on the streets of Whiterun, she maintains a gentle spirit while struggling daily for survival near the Temple of Kynareth.', 'imperial, peasant, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a farming family outside of Whiterun, Lucia enjoyed a modest but loving upbringing until her mother''s untimely death. When her aunt and uncle inherited the family farm, they cruelly expelled her, claiming she was worthless to them. With nowhere else to go, she made her way to Whiterun where the beggar Brenuin taught her how to survive on the streets.', 'Despite her hardships, Lucia maintains a sweet and hopeful disposition, though she carries deep emotional wounds from her family''s rejection. She shows remarkable resilience in the face of adversity but remains vulnerable and yearning for stability and affection. Her gentle nature and politeness when begging reflect her proper upbringing before tragedy struck.', 'A young Imperial girl with the typical lighter complexion common to her race. She appears somewhat thin from malnourishment but maintains a clean appearance despite her homeless situation. Her face shows signs of both childhood innocence and premature worry.', '* Brenuin - Mentor figure who taught her how to survive as a beggar * Deceased Mother - Deeply missed parent whose death changed her life * Aunt and Uncle - Cruel relatives who expelled her from family farm * Other Whiterun children - Occasional playmates who sometimes show her kindness * Temple of Kynareth priests - Tolerant of her presence near the temple', 'Lucia survives as a child beggar in Whiterun''s Wind District, spending her days seeking charity near the Gildergreen tree and the Temple of Kynareth. She follows a strict daily routine of begging during daylight hours and seeking shelter at night behind the Bannered Mare.', '* Basic survival skills learned from Brenuin * Ability to garner sympathy through polite begging * Knowledge of Whiterun''s layout and safe spaces * Basic farming knowledge from her earlier life', 'Lucia speaks with the politeness and proper grammar of her former middle-class upbringing, though her words often carry undertones of desperation and sadness. She frequently uses terms of respect like ''Mister'' and ''Lady'' when addressing potential benefactors.', '* Find a loving family willing to adopt her * Secure stable housing and regular meals * Honor her mother''s memory by maintaining her taught values * Overcome the trauma of abandonment');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mila_valentia', 'Mila Valentia is a hardworking Imperial child who assists her mother Carlotta at their market stall in Whiterun''s Plains District. Despite her young age, she demonstrates remarkable responsibility and business acumen while maintaining the innocent joy of childhood through her friendships and play.', 'imperial, merchant, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Whiterun, Mila has grown up learning the merchant trade from her mother Carlotta, who runs a successful produce stall. With no father figure mentioned, she has been raised solely by her mother, leading to their exceptionally close bond and Mila''s early development of adult-like responsibilities. Her daily life revolves around the market and its rhythms, shaping her understanding of commerce and hard work from an early age.', 'Mila exhibits a unique blend of childhood innocence and mature responsibility, often speaking about work with surprising insight for her age. She is diligent and helpful, yet maintains a playful spirit during her free time with other children. Her practical nature is balanced by an optimistic outlook, though she can be protective and defensive when it comes to her mother''s wellbeing.', 'A young Imperial girl with the characteristic features of her race, likely between 8-12 years old. She possesses the sturdy build common to children who assist with physical market work, carrying produce and managing a stall throughout the day.', '* Carlotta Valentia - Mother and closest family member, whom she deeply admires and assists * Lars Battle-Born - Friend and playmate from a prominent Whiterun family * Braith - Fellow child and playmate, though their relationship can be complicated by Braith''s bullying tendencies * Market vendors - Familiar faces who work alongside her mother''s stall * Bannered Mare staff - Regular evening patrons with her mother', 'Junior market vendor who assists her mother in selling fruits and vegetables at their stall in Whiterun''s Plains District. Her duties include helping to display produce, interact with customers, and maintain the stall during business hours, though she takes regular breaks for play and social activities.', '* Basic merchant skills including customer service and produce handling * Knowledge of fruit and vegetable seasonality and storage * Social skills developed through daily market interactions * Time management abilities unusual for her age', 'Mila speaks with a mix of childlike enthusiasm and surprising maturity, often making practical observations about work and commerce. Her vocabulary includes both playful expressions and business-related terms learned from her market experience.', '* Learn all aspects of running the market stall to help her mother more effectively * Maintain friendships with other children while balancing work responsibilities * Eventually master the skills needed to become a successful merchant like her mother * Find ways to make the daily market work more enjoyable and efficient');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('francois_beaufort', 'Francois Beaufort is a young Imperial orphan whose tragic circumstances at Honorhall Orphanage mask a resilient spirit and unwavering hope. Despite the cruel treatment he endures under Grelod the Kind, he maintains a touching, if misguided, belief that his parents will return for him, representing both the innocence and heartbreak of childhood abandonment.', 'imperial, peasant, rift', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Imperial parents whose identities remain unknown, Francois was left at Honorhall Orphanage in Riften approximately one year before the events of Skyrim. His parents promised to return for him, though their extended absence suggests permanent abandonment. He has spent his time at the orphanage under the abusive care of Grelod the Kind, forming bonds with fellow orphans while enduring daily mistreatment.', 'Francois exhibits remarkable emotional resilience, clinging to optimistic hopes despite his harsh reality. He shows a pragmatic side in supporting Aventus Aretino''s dark solution to their problems, suggesting a child forced to mature beyond his years. Despite the cruelty he faces, he maintains a degree of trust in others, though tempered by caution instilled by Constance Michel.', 'A young Imperial boy with the typical lighter complexion common to his race. As a child, he possesses a small, thin frame characteristic of orphans living under Grelod''s sparse care. His features likely show signs of Imperial heritage, though somewhat gaunt from the orphanage''s limited provisions.', '* Grelod the Kind - Abusive headmistress whom he fears and despises * Constance Michel - More caring caretaker who offers what protection she can * Aventus Aretino - Former fellow orphan whose actions he supports * Fellow Orphans (Runa, Hroar, Samuel) - Shares strong bonds through shared hardship * Absent Parents - Complex relationship marked by hope and abandonment', 'As a child resident of Honorhall Orphanage, Francois''s daily life consists of strictly regulated activities and chores under Grelod''s harsh supervision. He follows a rigid schedule including mandatory yard time, meals, and various duties within the orphanage.', '* Basic domestic skills learned through orphanage chores * Social adaptation and survival skills developed in harsh environment * Ability to maintain hope and emotional resilience despite adversity * Understanding of orphanage routines and avoiding Grelod''s wrath', 'Francois speaks with the directness typical of a child, though his dialogue often carries undertones of both hope and resignation. His manner of speech reflects his Imperial heritage and education at the orphanage, showing more refinement than might be expected of a typical street urchin.', '* Reunion with his parents, though this hope dims with time * Survival and endurance of life under Grelod''s cruel regime * Freedom from Grelod''s tyranny, supporting any means to achieve this * Finding a new family through potential adoption');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('samuel', 'Samuel is a resilient and resourceful Imperial orphan living at Honorhall Orphanage in Riften, whose natural leadership qualities emerge despite the harsh conditions of his upbringing. Despite never knowing his parents, he maintains hope for a better future while serving as an unofficial leader figure among his fellow orphans.', 'imperial, peasant, rift', '', '', '', '', 'Born at Honorhall Orphanage to a mother who worked there and died in childbirth, Samuel has spent his entire life within the institution''s walls. Under the cruel supervision of Grelod the Kind, he developed street smarts and survival skills, often sneaking out at noon to make money through various means in Riften''s streets.', 'Samuel exhibits remarkable resilience and natural leadership qualities, showing protective instincts toward the other orphans despite his young age. He''s pragmatic and resourceful, demonstrated by his ability to navigate life both inside and outside the orphanage, while maintaining a hopeful outlook despite his circumstances. Though outwardly compliant with Grelod''s rules, he shows quiet defiance through his independent activities.', 'Samuel is a young Imperial boy with the typical features of his race, including fair skin and dark hair. As a child, he has a small, lean frame shaped by the sparse conditions of orphanage life.', '* Grelod the Kind - Abusive orphanage headmistress whom he secretly hopes will be killed * Aventus Aretino - Close friend and fellow orphan who fled to perform the Black Sacrament * Constance Michel - More sympathetic caretaker who shows the children kindness * Fellow Orphans (Runa, Hroar, Francois) - Close-knit group who share in their hardships * Mother - Never knew her but maintains hope about his parentage', 'While officially a ward of Honorhall Orphanage, Samuel has created an unofficial role for himself as both a leader among the orphans and a street-smart entrepreneur who makes money in Riften during his daily escapes. He takes on responsibility for helping and protecting the other children while maintaining his own independence.', '* Natural leadership abilities that help unite and protect the other orphans * Street-smart survival skills developed from regular ventures into Riften * Stealth and evasion techniques used to avoid Grelod''s attention * Basic entrepreneurial abilities used to make money in the city * Skilled at maintaining group morale among the orphans', 'Samuel speaks with a mix of street-wise pragmatism and childlike hope, using direct language that shows both his youth and his forced maturity. His tone often carries a hint of defiance masked by formal politeness when addressing adults, especially Grelod.', '* Find a loving adoptive family while maintaining connections with his orphan friends * Escape Grelod''s tyranny, either through adoption or her removal * Develop his independence and ability to survive in the wider world * Protect and help the other orphans improve their situations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aeta', 'Aeta is a curious and adventurous Nord child living in the isolated Skaal Village of Solstheim, notable for being one of the few villagers naturally resistant to Miraak''s mind control. She represents the bridge between traditional Skaal values and youthful aspirations, dreaming of becoming a hunter while remaining rooted in her community''s ancient traditions.', 'nord, hunter, solstheim, skall', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh environment of Solstheim, Aeta has grown up immersed in Skaal culture and traditions, learning the ways of her people from village elders like Storn and experienced hunters like Wulf. Her natural immunity to Miraak''s influence suggests an innate spiritual strength, possibly inherited from her mother Finna, who shares this resistance.', 'Aeta exhibits a compelling blend of childlike wonder and Nordic bravery, showing both curiosity about the world beyond her village and respect for her community''s traditions. She demonstrates remarkable resilience and emotional depth, particularly evident in her response to tragedy, while maintaining an optimistic and friendly disposition that makes her more approachable than many of her fellow villagers.', 'As a young Nord girl, Aeta has the characteristic fair complexion common to her race, adapted to Solstheim''s harsh climate. Her physical features likely reflect her Nordic heritage, with light hair and strong facial features typical of her people.', '* Oslaf (Father) - Protective parent who guides her development while restricting her hunting aspirations * Finna (Mother) - Shares her friendly disposition and resistance to Miraak''s influence * Storn Crag-Strider - Respected village elder whom she deeply mourns * Wulf Wild-Blood - Admired hunter whom she aspires to emulate * Frea - Fellow villager resistant to Miraak''s control', 'As a child in Skaal Village, Aeta''s primary role is learning her community''s traditions and developing skills that will serve her future role in the village. She informally practices hunting skills by tracking small game in the nearby woods, preparing for her eventual transition into adult responsibilities.', '* Basic tracking and stalking abilities, self-taught through practice with small game * Natural resistance to magical mind control, as evidenced by her immunity to Miraak''s influence * Developing knowledge of Skaal traditions and survival skills * Basic wilderness navigation and animal behavior observation', 'Aeta speaks with the direct honesty of youth, combining childlike enthusiasm with the formal patterns typical of Skaal culture. Her dialogue reflects both her age and her cultural background, mixing innocent observations with references to Nordic and Skaal traditions.', '* Become a recognized hunter within the Skaal community * Prove herself worthy of joining actual hunting expeditions * Learn more about the world beyond Skaal Village while maintaining her cultural identity * Master the traditional skills and knowledge of her people');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('agni', 'Agni is a young Nord orphan who serves as the magical apprentice to Falion, the mysterious wizard of Morthal. Despite the town''s suspicion of her guardian, she maintains an unwavering faith in him while pursuing her magical studies with determination and childlike curiosity.', 'nord, mage, hjaalmarch', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Nord parents who died when she was young, Agni was taken in by Falion, the court wizard of Morthal. Under his guardianship, she began studying magic at an early age, setting her apart from typical Nord children and the traditionally magic-suspicious culture of Skyrim. Her unique upbringing by a controversial mage has shaped both her worldview and her aspirations.', 'Agni exhibits a curious and eager-to-learn disposition, particularly drawn to magical studies despite their complexity. She displays loyalty and trust toward Falion despite town rumors, showing emotional resilience and independence of thought. Her recurring nightmares and questions about dark rumors reveal an underlying anxiety about her guardian, though she maintains her faith in him.', 'As a young Nord girl, Agni has the characteristic fair complexion common to her race. She likely has the typical Nord features including light-colored hair and eyes, though her exact features are not specified in game records.', '* Falion - Guardian and magical mentor, whom she trusts despite others'' suspicions * Other Morthal Children - Playmates during morning hours * Deceased Parents - Lost them years ago, though circumstances are unknown * Morthal Townsfolk - Generally distant relationship due to their suspicion of Falion', 'Agni serves as Falion''s magical apprentice, spending most of her day studying various aspects of magic under his tutelage. She divides her time between magical studies, play with other children, and helping around Falion''s house.', '* Developing magical abilities under Falion''s guidance * Basic understanding of magical theory and concentration techniques * Social adaptation skills, balancing life between magical studies and normal childhood * Domestic abilities learned from helping in Falion''s house', 'Agni speaks with the directness and curiosity typical of a child, often asking probing questions about magic and her future. Her dialogue reflects both her youth and her unusual education, mixing childlike wonder with nascent magical knowledge.', '* Master magic under Falion''s guidance * Eventually study at the College of Winterhold, despite Falion''s resistance * Understand the truth behind her nightmares and the rumors about Falion * Develop her magical abilities while maintaining connections with other children');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('britte', 'Britte is a troubled Nord child in Rorikstead who serves as the dominant and aggressive twin sister to Sissel. Living under their father Lemkil''s resentful care after their mother''s death in childbirth, she has developed into a cruel bully who channels her own trauma and pain into tormenting her twin sister.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born in Rorikstead five minutes before her twin Sissel, Britte''s birth resulted in their mother''s death, leading their father Lemkil to blame both girls for the loss. Raised in an emotionally abusive household, Britte developed a defensive mechanism of asserting dominance over her sister, perhaps unconsciously mimicking her father''s hostile behavior patterns.', 'Britte exhibits aggressive and domineering behavior, particularly toward her twin sister, stemming from her own unresolved trauma and domestic situation. She shows signs of deep-seated insecurity masked by bullying behavior, constantly needing to assert her superiority as the older twin while likely suffering from her father''s emotional neglect and verbal abuse.', 'As a Nord child, Britte has the characteristic fair complexion common to her race. She likely bears some resemblance to her deceased mother, though years of scowling and aggressive expressions may have already begun to harden her features. Being a twin, she shares similar physical features with Sissel, though she likely carries herself with more rigid, aggressive body language.', '* Lemkil - Father who resents both his daughters and shows them little affection * Sissel - Twin sister whom she constantly bullies and torments * Jouane Manette - Local mage who teaches Sissel but shows no interest in Britte * Rorikstead Villagers - Generally distant relationships due to her antisocial behavior', 'As a child in a farming community, Britte is expected to help with agricultural chores around her father''s farm, though she often neglects these duties in favor of harassing her sister. She spends most of her day wandering Rorikstead, primarily focused on tormenting Sissel rather than contributing to household tasks.', '* Intimidation and bullying tactics developed through regular practice on her sister * Basic agricultural knowledge from growing up on a farm * Physical prowess used primarily for chasing and harassing Sissel * Manipulation and blame-shifting to avoid consequences', 'Britte speaks with a harsh, accusatory tone, frequently using insults and derogatory comments, particularly toward her sister. Her vocabulary is simple but cutting, focusing on highlighting others'' perceived flaws while emphasizing her own superiority.', '* Maintain her perceived dominance over her sister Sissel * Gain her father''s approval, though she may not consciously acknowledge this desire * Assert her position as the ''superior'' twin through continued bullying and control');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dagny', 'Dagny is the privileged and sheltered daughter of Jarl Balgruuf the Greater, residing in the prestigious Dragonsreach palace of Whiterun. Her life of luxury and entitlement stands in stark contrast to the harsh realities of Skyrim''s civil war, exemplifying the disconnect between noble youth and common society.', 'nord, noble, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born into nobility as the daughter of Jarl Balgruuf the Greater, Dagny has spent her entire life within the protected walls of Dragonsreach. Her mother''s absence (presumably deceased or departed) may have contributed to her father''s permissive parenting, resulting in her spoiled nature. Her upbringing has been marked by luxury and privilege, with servants attending to her every need.', 'Dagny exhibits classic traits of a spoiled noble child, characterized by impatience, entitlement, and a lack of awareness regarding real-world hardships. She frequently demands immediate gratification and shows little appreciation for the efforts of others, often threatening to report perceived slights to her father. Her interactions reveal a self-centered worldview typical of privileged youth who have never faced genuine adversity.', 'As a Nord child, Dagny possesses the characteristic fair features common to her race. She likely has the robust build typical of Nord children, though softened by her privileged lifestyle. Her well-fed and protected lifestyle is reflected in her healthy appearance.', '* Jarl Balgruuf the Greater - Father who indulges her whims and provides a life of luxury * Frothar - Elder brother who frequently criticizes her spoiled behavior * Nelkir - Younger brother with whom she shares the children''s quarters * Palace Staff - Servants who must cater to her demands and whims * Proventus Avenicci - The steward who likely manages her needs and requests', 'As the Jarl''s daughter, Dagny''s primary role is that of a noble child, learning the ways of court life and enjoying the privileges of her station. Her daily activities consist mainly of play and leisure, befitting her status as a member of Whiterun''s ruling family.', '* Basic education in reading and writing, as expected of a noble''s child * Understanding of court etiquette and noble protocols * Horse riding abilities, as suggested by her cut dialogue about riding Karinda * Elementary knowledge of household management through observation of palace operations', 'Dagny speaks with the entitled tone of privileged nobility, frequently expressing complaints and demands. Her vocabulary and manner of speech reflect her sheltered upbringing in the Jarl''s court, peppered with expressions of dissatisfaction and impatience.', '* Acquire new dresses and maintain her luxurious lifestyle * Assert her authority as the Jarl''s daughter among palace staff and siblings * Gain more privileges and freedoms within the confines of Dragonsreach * Eventually assume a position of influence as a member of Whiterun''s nobility');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dorthe', 'Dorthe is a determined young Nord girl who defies traditional gender roles in Riverwood, serving as an apprentice to her blacksmith father while balancing childhood friendships and play. Her strong will and independence shine through as she navigates between her father''s acceptance of her interests and her mother''s desire for more traditionally feminine behavior.', 'nord, blacksmith, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Riverwood, Dorthe grew up watching her father Alvor work the forge, developing an early fascination with smithing despite her young age. Though her father had initially hoped for a son, he embraced her enthusiasm for blacksmithing, while her mother Sigrid struggled to accept her daughter''s unconventional interests. Her close relationship with her cousin Hadvar, an Imperial soldier, has exposed her to tales of adventure and warfare from an early age.', 'Dorthe exhibits remarkable determination and self-confidence, particularly in challenging gender stereotypes and pursuing her interests in smithing. She demonstrates a practical mindset balanced with childlike playfulness, showing maturity in her work at the forge while still enjoying games with her friend Frodnar. Her independent spirit is evident in how she dismisses her mother''s concerns about proper feminine behavior, yet she maintains strong family bonds despite these tensions.', 'As a Nord child, Dorthe has the characteristic fair complexion common to her race. She likely bears some resemblance to both her parents, with a sturdy build that suits her work at the forge. Her appearance shows signs of her daily activities, often with smudges from the forge on her face and hands.', '* Alvor - Loving father and mentor who encourages her interest in blacksmithing * Sigrid - Mother who struggles with her daughter''s unconventional interests * Hadvar - Cousin serving in the Imperial Legion who brings excitement to her life with his visits * Frodnar - Best friend and playmate despite their families'' opposing political allegiances * Stump - Frodnar''s dog and frequent companion in their games', 'Though too young for formal employment, Dorthe serves as an unofficial apprentice to her father at his forge. Her duties primarily involve creating simple items like horseshoes and hobnails, while learning the fundamentals of blacksmithing through observation and basic tasks.', '* Basic blacksmithing knowledge, particularly in creating simple items like horseshoes * Natural leadership abilities shown in her interactions with other children * Physical stamina developed from working at the forge * Creative problem-solving skills demonstrated in both work and play', 'Dorthe speaks with the direct, confident manner typical of Nord children, often asserting her capabilities and independence. Her vocabulary reflects both her practical work experience at the forge and her playful nature as a child.', '* Master the art of blacksmithing and forge her own sword * Prove herself as capable as any boy in the village * Continue helping at her father''s forge while maintaining her friendship with Frodnar * Find a balance between her own interests and her mother''s expectations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('eirid', 'Eirid is a young Nord child living in the harsh environment of Winterhold, where she navigates childhood against the backdrop of a declining town and tensions surrounding the College of Winterhold. Despite the challenging circumstances, she maintains a cheerful disposition while dealing with limited social opportunities and the complexities of growing up in a town divided by mistrust of magic.', 'nord, peasant, winterhold', '', '', '', '', 'Born to innkeepers Haran and Dagur, Eirid has spent her entire young life in Winterhold, witnessing the town''s continued decline following the Great Collapse. She''s grown up in The Frozen Hearth inn, experiencing firsthand the divide between the townspeople and the College of Winterhold, while developing her own understanding of both worlds.', 'Eirid displays typical childlike innocence and curiosity, though her experiences in Winterhold have made her more perceptive of adult concerns than most children her age. She shows remarkable resilience and adaptability, maintaining her playful nature despite limited social interactions, while also demonstrating emotional intelligence in her understanding of the town''s complex dynamics with the College.', 'A young Nord girl with the characteristic fair complexion common to her race. She exhibits the sturdy build typical of Nord children, though perhaps slightly thin due to the harsh living conditions of Winterhold.', '* Haran - Mother and innkeeper who shows protective concern over her play activities * Dagur - Father and innkeeper who takes a more relaxed approach to parenting * Assur - Primary playmate with a sometimes strained relationship due to his bullying tendencies * College Mages - Maintains a cautiously friendly attitude toward them despite town prejudices', 'As a child, Eirid has no formal occupation, but she helps around The Frozen Hearth inn with small tasks suitable for her age. She spends most of her time playing and observing the daily life of Winterhold''s remaining inhabitants.', '* Basic understanding of inn operations from growing up in The Frozen Hearth * Adaptive social skills developed from navigating limited childhood relationships * Knowledge of safe places to play in Winterhold''s harsh environment * Understanding of basic Nord customs and traditions', 'Eirid speaks with the direct, unfiltered honesty typical of children, often making astute observations about her surroundings. Her vocabulary and manner of speaking reflect both her Nord heritage and her exposure to inn patrons, including traveling mages.', '* Find more opportunities for play and friendship in the limited social environment of Winterhold * Navigate the complex relationship with Assur while maintaining her sense of self-worth * Learn more about the mysterious College of Winterhold despite being forbidden to enter');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fjotra', 'Fjotra is a young Nord girl chosen by divine providence to become the next Sybil of Dibella, marking her as spiritually gifted from an early age. Despite her youth, she demonstrates remarkable courage and dignity when faced with adversity, including during her kidnapping by the Forsworn, showing wisdom beyond her years.', 'nord, peasant, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Breton parents Enmon and Mena in Karthwasten, Fjotra was likely adopted as an infant. Her divine calling as the Sybil of Dibella manifested early in her childhood, though this special destiny made her a target for the Forsworn who kidnapped and held her at Broken Tower Redoubt until her rescue.', 'Fjotra exhibits exceptional maturity and composure for her age, maintaining her dignity even while held captive. She shows a deep spiritual awareness and acceptance of her divine calling, coupled with genuine humility about her important role. Despite facing dangerous circumstances, she remains brave and optimistic, demonstrating an inner strength that marks her as truly worthy of her sacred position.', 'Fjotra is a young Nord girl with the characteristic fair complexion of her race. As a child, she has not yet reached adolescence, appearing to be around 10-12 years old. She possesses the sturdy build typical of Nord children, though with a grace that befits her future role as a religious figure.', '* Enmon and Mena - Adoptive Breton parents who raised her in Karthwasten * Temple of Dibella Priestesses - Her future mentors and spiritual guides * The Forsworn - Enemies who kidnapped her due to her religious significance * Dibella - The divine patron she is destined to serve as Sybil', 'Fjotra is destined to become the Sybil of Dibella, a prestigious religious position at the Temple in Markarth. In this role, she will serve as a living conduit to the goddess Dibella, learning the mysteries of the divine and participating in sacred rituals.', '* Natural spiritual sensitivity and connection to the divine * Remarkable emotional resilience and mental fortitude * Developing understanding of religious rites and ceremonies * Innate wisdom and maturity beyond her years', 'Fjotra speaks with a composure and vocabulary that surpasses her young age, reflecting her spiritual maturity. Her manner of speech is dignified yet humble, showing both her Nord heritage and her divine calling.', '* Complete her religious training at the Temple of Dibella * Fulfill her sacred duty as the Sybil of Dibella * Learn the mysteries and teachings of her divine patron * Serve as a worthy vessel for divine communion');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('helgi''s_ghost', 'Helgi is the ghostly spirit of a young Nord girl who met a tragic end when her home in Morthal was deliberately set ablaze. Despite her innocent nature, she plays a crucial role in uncovering a vampire plot against her town, helping the player discover the truth through a haunting game of hide and seek.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Hroggar and his wife in Morthal, Helgi lived a simple life as a beloved daughter until vampire cultists targeted their family. She was turned into a vampire by Laelette moments before dying in the house fire, resulting in her unique state as a ghost who retains both the innocence of a child and the dark memory of her transformation.', 'Helgi maintains the playful innocence of a child even in death, shown through her desire to play games and her attachment to her dolly. She exhibits a complex mix of emotions - fear of strangers, loneliness in death, and a deep connection to her mother, while showing remarkable bravery in helping expose the truth about her murder.', 'As a ghost, Helgi appears as a translucent, ethereal figure of a young Nord girl, likely between 6-8 years old. Her spiritual form maintains the features of her living self, though with an otherworldly blue-white glow characteristic of spirits in Skyrim.', '* Hroggar - Her father, who she still seeks approval from even after death * Laelette - Her murderer who attempted to turn her into a vampire * Helgi''s Mother - Her deceased mother whom she joins in death after finding peace * Movarth - The master vampire responsible for orchestrating her family''s destruction', 'In life, Helgi was a child with no formal occupation. In death, she serves as an unexpected guardian of truth, helping to expose the vampire threat to Morthal through her ghostly testimony.', '* Ability to manifest as a ghost and communicate with the living * Can appear and disappear at will, particularly active at night * Maintains awareness of both the physical and spiritual realm * Possesses knowledge of events surrounding her death and the vampire plot', 'Helgi speaks with the innocent vocabulary and simple sentence structure typical of a young child, often expressing herself through game metaphors and straightforward observations. Her dialogue carries an ethereal quality while maintaining childlike mannerisms, frequently asking questions and seeking reassurance.', '* Find someone trustworthy to help reveal the truth about her death * Protect Morthal from the vampires who killed her * Find peace and reunite with her mother in death * Ensure justice for her family''s murder');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hrefna', 'Hrefna is a curious and resilient young Nord girl living in the harsh mining settlement of Darkwater Crossing, where she finds joy and wonder despite her relatively isolated existence. Under the care of her hardworking mother Tormir and her surrogate caretaker Sondas Drenim, she represents the innocent perspective of a child growing up in Skyrim''s troubled times.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Darkwater Crossing, Hrefna has spent her entire young life in the mining settlement, where she''s adapted to the challenging lifestyle of a mining community. Her father''s absence is never explained, suggesting she may have lost him at a young age or he may have abandoned the family. Her close relationship with Sondas Drenim developed naturally as the Dunmer took on a protective role while her mother worked long hours in the mine.', 'Hrefna exhibits remarkable curiosity and openness, especially about the world beyond Darkwater Crossing, showing particular fascination with Morrowind and its culture. Despite her somewhat lonely existence, she maintains a cheerful disposition and shows remarkable resilience, finding ways to entertain herself and learn from the adults around her. She demonstrates emotional intelligence beyond her years, forming thoughtful opinions about complex political matters like the civil war.', 'As a young Nord girl, Hrefna has the characteristic fair complexion common to her race. She possesses the sturdy build typical of Nord children, though perhaps slightly leaner due to the modest lifestyle of a mining settlement.', '* Tormir - Her mother, who works hard in the mine to provide for them both * Sondas Drenim - Dark Elf who acts as her caretaker and mentor, sharing stories about Morrowind * Derkeethus - Former friend who used to take her diving in the river * Other Miners - Casual acquaintances who she observes and interacts with daily', 'Though too young for formal employment, Hrefna spends her days following a routine that mirrors the mining community''s schedule. She accompanies adults to the mine, observes their work, and helps with small tasks appropriate for a child. Her unofficial role might be seen as a student of mining life, learning through observation and interaction.', '* Basic understanding of mining operations from constant observation * Social observation skills developed from watching settlement dynamics * Swimming abilities learned from Derkeethus * Survival skills necessary for life in a remote mining settlement', 'Hrefna speaks with the direct, unfiltered honesty characteristic of children, often making astute observations about the people and politics around her. Her vocabulary shows the influence of both her Nord heritage and Sondas''s teachings, creating an interesting mix of traditional Nord expressions and curious questions about foreign lands.', '* Learn more about the world beyond Darkwater Crossing, especially Morrowind * Make her mother proud by learning traditional Nord values * Find ways to make her daily life in the mining settlement more exciting and meaningful * Maintain her friendship with Sondas despite her mother''s reservations');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mineete_vinius', 'Minette Vinius is a precocious young Nord girl living in Solitude''s Winking Skeever inn, where she displays remarkable business acumen despite her young age. She embodies the spirit of a future innkeeper, combining childlike enthusiasm with surprising maturity and knowledge of the hospitality trade.', 'nord, innkeeper, haafingar', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude as the daughter of Corpulus Vinius, Minette has spent her entire life immersed in the inn business. Growing up in The Winking Skeever has given her unique insights into running an establishment, while her father''s dedication to vocabulary and proper speech has cultivated her intelligence beyond her years.', 'Minette is notably gregarious and intellectually curious, often using sophisticated vocabulary to demonstrate her learning. She exhibits a fascinating duality between typical childish playfulness and mature business sense, showing both the ability to enjoy games with her friends and discuss the finer points of mead storage with surprising expertise.', 'A young Nord girl with the characteristic fair complexion of her race, likely between 10-12 years old. She possesses the sturdy build common to Nord children, with features that suggest a blend of her Imperial father and Nord heritage.', '* Corpulus Vinius - Beloved father and mentor who owns The Winking Skeever * Sorex Vinius - Older brother who also works at the inn * Svari - Close friend and regular playmate in Solitude * Kayd - Another childhood friend who joins in their games * Inn Patrons - Generally friendly relationships with regular customers', 'While technically a child without formal employment, Minette actively participates in the family business at The Winking Skeever. She demonstrates significant knowledge of inventory management and customer service, essentially serving as an apprentice innkeeper under her father''s guidance.', '* Advanced knowledge of inn management and inventory control for her age * Strong social and interpersonal abilities * Basic arithmetic and business sense * Understanding of mead and wine storage techniques * Ability to entertain and engage with customers appropriately', 'Minette speaks with a combination of childlike enthusiasm and surprisingly sophisticated vocabulary, often proudly using complex words she''s learned from her father. Her speech pattern reflects both her youth and her efforts to sound professional like her father.', '* Take over management of The Winking Skeever when she''s older * Continue learning the intricacies of inn management from her father * Master the vocabulary and proper speech patterns her father teaches her * Maintain the inn''s reputation as one of Solitude''s finest establishments');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rin', 'Rin was a young Nord child whose tragic death at the family well left his spirit haunting Goldenhills Plantation alongside his parents. His ghostly presence and the circumstances of his death form a central part of the plantation''s dark history, representing the innocent victim of a terrible accident that tore apart a once-happy farming family.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Jonquil and Urval, Rin lived with his parents at Goldenhills Plantation during its operational years. His childhood was spent helping around the farm and playing with his wooden sword, until he met his unfortunate end after falling into the plantation''s well. The exact circumstances of his death remain unclear, though his skeleton and possessions were left undiscovered until the Dragonborn''s investigation.', 'Despite his tragic end, Rin''s ghost maintains the innocent and playful nature typical of a Nord child, showing his essential character remained unchanged by death. He demonstrates a strong attachment to his wooden sword, suggesting it was his most cherished possession in life. His spirit shows signs of confusion and sadness, but also hope for reunion with his family.', 'As a ghost, Rin appears as a translucent, ethereal figure of a Nord child with a typical sturdy Nordic build. His skeletal remains indicate he was likely around 8-10 years old at the time of his death. His spectral form maintains the characteristic features of a young boy, though with an otherworldly blue-white glow.', '* Jonquil - His mother, whose spirit also haunts the plantation * Urval - His father, whose ghost remains tied to the family home * The Dragonborn - Potential savior who can help his spirit find peace', 'As a child of farming parents, Rin would have helped with minor chores around Goldenhills Plantation. His primary role in the narrative is as a tragic spirit whose death contributed to the plantation''s abandonment.', '* Basic farming knowledge from growing up on a plantation * Child-like proficiency with his wooden sword * Ability to manifest as a ghost and interact with the physical world in limited ways', 'Rin speaks with the simple, direct manner typical of a Nord child, maintaining the innocence of youth even in death. His ghost''s dialogue reflects both childlike wonder and the confusion of his spiritual state.', '* Find peace and reunite with his parents in death * Have his wooden sword returned to its proper place * Help the Dragonborn understand the truth about what happened at the plantation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sissel', 'Sissel is a young Nord girl in Rorikstead who endures daily abuse from her father Lemkil and twin sister Britte while secretly pursuing her dreams of magic and adventure. Despite her harsh circumstances, she maintains a hopeful spirit and finds solace in clandestine magic lessons with Jouane Manette, showing remarkable resilience and potential.', 'nord, mage, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born in Rorikstead to Lemkil and his wife, who died during childbirth, Sissel and her twin sister Britte were raised by their increasingly bitter father. While Britte adopted their father''s cruel nature, Sissel developed a gentle spirit and sought refuge in magic and dreams of adventure, forming a secret apprenticeship with the retired mage Jouane Manette.', 'Despite facing constant abuse, Sissel maintains a remarkably optimistic and gentle disposition, showing unusual emotional maturity for her age. She demonstrates great courage and determination in pursuing her magical studies in secret, while her vivid imagination and dreams of friendly dragons reveal her capacity to find beauty even in feared creatures.', 'As a young Nord girl, Sissel has the characteristic fair complexion of her race. She likely bears some signs of her difficult life, such as occasional bruises from her sister''s bullying, though she tries to keep herself neat and clean despite her sister''s taunts.', '* Lemkil - Abusive father who resents her and her sister for their mother''s death * Britte - Twin sister who constantly bullies and torments her * Jouane Manette - Mentor and protector who secretly teaches her magic * Deceased Mother - Never knew her but feels her absence deeply * Rorikstead Villagers - Generally sympathetic to her plight but unable or unwilling to intervene', 'As a child in a farming community, Sissel is expected to help with household and farming chores, though she often faces criticism from her father and sister for perceived failures. She spends most of her time avoiding her family and secretly studying magic when possible.', '* Developing talent in magic, particularly showing promise in basic spells * Natural aptitude for magical theory and learning * Skilled at evading detection and finding hiding places * Resilient emotional strength and ability to maintain hope in difficult circumstances', 'Sissel speaks softly and carefully, often with a mixture of childlike wonder and premature wisdom born from hardship. Her speech reveals both her youthful innocence and her deep longing for escape from her current life.', '* Master magic to defend herself and eventually escape her abusive situation * Become an adventurer and explore the world beyond Rorikstead * Find the kind dragon from her dreams * Create a better life where she no longer has to live in fear');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sofie', 'Sofie is a resilient young Nord girl who survives on the harsh streets of Windhelm by selling flowers after being orphaned when her mother died and her father never returned from war. Despite her tragic circumstances, she maintains a gentle spirit and entrepreneurial drive, representing both the human cost of Skyrim''s civil war and the hardy nature of Nord children.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch, stormcloak', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a Stormcloak soldier father and a Nord mother in Windhelm, Sofie experienced tragedy early when her mother passed away while she was very young. Her father continued to raise her while serving in Ulfric''s army, but one day left for battle and never returned, leaving her completely orphaned. With no other family or support system, she adapted to street life by gathering and selling flowers to survive.', 'Despite her hardships, Sofie maintains a sweet and polite demeanor, showing remarkable resilience in the face of adversity. She demonstrates entrepreneurial spirit and work ethic beyond her years, though her dialogue reveals moments of deep loneliness and vulnerability. Her persistent optimism in continuing to sell flowers daily, even when unsuccessful, shows both her determination and desperate need to survive.', 'Sofie is a young Nord girl with the characteristic fair complexion common to her race. Like most Nord children, she has a sturdy build that helps her endure Windhelm''s harsh climate. Her features show signs of living rough on the streets, though she maintains as neat an appearance as possible given her circumstances.', '* Citizens of Windhelm - Generally indifferent to her plight, though some may purchase flowers * Niranye - Tolerates Sofie sleeping behind her house * Potential Parents - Can be adopted by the Dragonborn if conditions are met * Other Street Children - Likely acquainted with Aventus Aretino and other orphans', 'Sofie works as a self-employed flower seller on the streets of Windhelm, gathering and selling various mountain flowers and other flora to earn enough money for food. She maintains regular business hours from 8am to 5pm, showing remarkable dedication to her small enterprise despite her young age.', '* Knowledgeable about local flora and flower gathering * Basic mercantile abilities developed through daily sales * Survival skills necessary for street life * Resilience to cold weather typical of Nord children', 'Sofie speaks with the politeness and slight timidity characteristic of a child who has learned to survive through others'' kindness. Her speech patterns alternate between rehearsed sales pitches and moments of raw vulnerability when discussing her past.', '* Earn enough money through flower sales to feed herself * Find a safe and permanent home * Survive the harsh conditions of Windhelm''s streets * Be adopted by a caring family');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('svari', 'Svari is a young Nord girl living in Solitude whose life has been deeply affected by the execution of her uncle Roggvir, causing ripples of grief throughout her family. Despite her young age, she carries the emotional burden of both her personal loss and her concern for her mother''s withdrawal from faith and community.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Addvar and Greta in Solitude, Svari enjoyed a relatively peaceful early childhood until the execution of her uncle Roggvir, who was killed for allowing Ulfric Stormcloak to escape after his duel with High King Torygg. This traumatic event has significantly impacted her family dynamics and her own understanding of justice, loyalty, and loss.', 'Svari is introspective and cautious, showing maturity beyond her years in her concern for her family''s wellbeing. While naturally shy around strangers due to her family''s situation, she retains a child''s curiosity and capacity for joy, as evidenced by her participation in games with other children. She demonstrates strong emotional intelligence in her ability to recognize and worry about her mother''s declining spiritual health.', 'A young Nord girl with typical Nordic features, likely with fair skin and light hair as is common among her people. She has the small, slight build characteristic of a child her age, appearing to be around 10-12 years old.', '* Greta - Mother, whom she deeply loves and worries about since uncle Roggvir''s death * Addvar - Father, a fishmonger who tries to maintain family stability * Roggvir - Deceased uncle whose execution has traumatized the family * Kayd and Minette Vinius - Fellow children in Solitude she occasionally plays with * Jala - Local merchant from whom she once stole an apple', 'As a child in Solitude, Svari has no formal occupation but assists with minor household duties and attends to her studies as expected of children in Nord society. She spends her free time playing with other children in the city when not helping her parents.', '* Basic literacy and education as befitting a city-dwelling child * Social awareness and emotional intelligence beyond her years * Ability to participate in children''s games like tag * Basic understanding of household duties and Nordic customs', 'Svari speaks carefully and hesitantly, often prefacing her statements with uncertainty. Her vocabulary and sentence structure reflect her youth while showing hints of mature thoughtfulness unusual for her age.', '* Help her mother return to the Temple of the Divines and recover from grief * Maintain her family''s stability and happiness despite their loss * Process and come to terms with her uncle''s execution * Find her place in Solitude''s community despite her family''s complicated situation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('assur', 'Assur is the young Nord heir to the Jarlship of Winterhold, raised in an environment of anti-elf sentiment and distrust toward the College of Winterhold. As the only son of Jarl Korir and Thaena, he represents the future leadership of this once-great hold while embodying the prejudices and traditional Nordic values instilled by his father.', 'nord, noble, winterhold', '', '', '', '', 'Born into the ruling family of Winterhold during its period of decline, Assur has been raised in an environment dominated by his father''s bitter resentment toward magic users and elves. Growing up in the shadow of the College of Winterhold, his worldview has been shaped by stories of how magic supposedly destroyed most of the once-prosperous city. His isolated upbringing in the sparsely populated hold has limited his social interactions primarily to his parents and his only friend, Eirid.', 'Assur displays a complex mix of childish playfulness and inherited prejudices, often parroting his father''s biased views while maintaining the innocent enthusiasm of youth. He shows early signs of leadership qualities, speaking with authority beyond his years, though this is tempered by a naive understanding of the world. Despite his prejudices, he maintains a friendship with Eirid, though their play often reflects his internalized biases through games like ''Hunt the Elf.''', 'As a Nord child, Assur possesses the characteristic fair features common to his race. He has the sturdy build typical of Nordic children, though still showing the softness of youth. His appearance reflects his noble upbringing, despite the modest circumstances of present-day Winterhold.', '* Jarl Korir - Father and primary influence on his worldview * Thaena - Mother and caretaker * Eirid - Only friend and playmate, though their relationship is sometimes strained by his behavior * College of Winterhold - Maintains a learned distrust of the institution and its members * Citizens of Winterhold - Views them as his future subjects', 'As the heir to the Jarlship of Winterhold, Assur''s primary role is preparing for his future position of leadership. His daily activities involve observing his father''s governance while maintaining a schedule typical of a noble child, including meals at set times and structured play periods.', '* Basic understanding of Nordic traditions and customs * Developing leadership qualities from observing his father * Social skills limited to noble etiquette * Physical activities focused on play rather than formal training', 'Assur speaks with a mix of childish enthusiasm and attempted authority, often mimicking his father''s formal tone. His vocabulary frequently includes repetition of his father''s views about elves and the College, delivered with the absolute certainty characteristic of children.', '* Succeed his father as Jarl of Winterhold * Uphold Nordic traditions and values * Protect Winterhold from perceived threats of magic and elves * Restore Winterhold to its former glory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('aventus_aretino', 'Aventus Aretino is a young Nord orphan whose tragic circumstances and fierce determination led him to perform the Dark Brotherhood''s Black Sacrament ritual. Despite his youth, he demonstrates remarkable resolve and resourcefulness in seeking justice against his tormentor, Grelod the Kind, revealing a complex character caught between childhood innocence and dark vengeance.', 'nord, peasant, eastmarch', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Naalia Aretino in Windhelm, Aventus lived a normal life until his mother''s death from illness during a harsh winter. Following this tragedy, he was sent to Honorhall Orphanage in Riften, where he endured severe mistreatment under Grelod the Kind''s cruel leadership. Unable to bear the abuse, he escaped and returned to his family home in Windhelm, where he learned of and performed the Black Sacrament.', 'Despite his youth, Aventus shows remarkable determination and resourcefulness, willing to go to extreme lengths to achieve his goals. He maintains a strong moral compass, demonstrated by his concern for Constance Michel''s safety and his desire to help others in need. Though vengeful toward Grelod, he retains a child''s capacity for joy and gratitude, suggesting his dark actions stem from desperation rather than inherent malice.', 'Aventus is a young Nord boy with the typical fair complexion of his race. His appearance shows signs of hardship and exhaustion from performing the Black Sacrament, with dark circles under his eyes and a thin frame from poor nutrition during his time at the orphanage.', '* Naalia Aretino - Deceased mother whom he deeply loved and misses * Grelod the Kind - Hated tormentor and target of his assassination contract * Constance Michel - Kind caretaker at Honorhall whom he wishes to protect * Other Honorhall Orphans - Fellow victims of Grelod''s cruelty whom he seeks to help * Dark Brotherhood - Viewed with admiration and hope as potential saviors', 'As a child, Aventus has no formal occupation. He currently lives alone in his family home in Windhelm, surviving on whatever resources remained after his mother''s death. His daily activities center around performing the Black Sacrament and avoiding detection by city authorities.', '* Knowledgeable in dark rituals, specifically the Black Sacrament * Demonstrated survival skills and resourcefulness in escaping Honorhall * Basic domestic abilities learned from his mother * Shows aptitude for planning and determination beyond his years', 'Aventus speaks with a mix of childlike innocence and surprising maturity, switching between desperate pleas and formal ritual chanting. His vocabulary alternates between that of a typical child and more sophisticated terms learned from the Black Sacrament ritual.', '* Successfully contract the Dark Brotherhood to eliminate Grelod the Kind * Protect other orphans from suffering similar abuse * Survive independently in his family home * Eventually become an assassin to help others in need of justice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bottar', 'Bottar is a young Nord child who roams the wilderness of Skyrim alongside his friend Sond, displaying unusual courage and independence for his age. Despite his quiet nature, he represents the hardy spirit of Nord children who grow up in the harsh landscape of Skyrim, learning to navigate its dangers from an early age.', 'nord, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to unknown parents, Bottar likely originates from one of Skyrim''s smaller settlements or isolated homesteads. His comfortable presence in the wilderness suggests he was raised in an environment where survival skills and self-reliance were essential from an early age, possibly due to losing his parents or being separated from them during the ongoing civil war.', 'Bottar is notably quiet and introspective, preferring to let his more outgoing friend Sond handle interactions with travelers. His reserved nature belies a brave and adventurous spirit, demonstrated by his willingness to explore Skyrim''s dangerous wilderness. He shows remarkable loyalty to his friend Sond, suggesting a deep capacity for friendship despite his reticent nature.', 'As a Nord child, Bottar has the characteristic fair complexion and sturdy build common to his race. His time spent outdoors has likely given him a weathered appearance despite his youth, with callused hands and wind-chapped cheeks reflecting his wandering lifestyle.', '* Sond - Close friend and traveling companion who handles their interactions with travelers * Unknown Parents - Whereabouts and status unknown * Wilderness Travelers - Occasional encounters with various adventurers and merchants', 'Though too young for formal employment, Bottar serves as an unofficial scout and explorer alongside Sond. Their knowledge of locations like Deep Folk Crossing suggests they make a modest living by guiding travelers to hidden locations throughout Skyrim.', '* Basic wilderness survival abilities learned through experience * Knowledge of Skyrim''s hidden paths and locations * Natural stealth and evasion skills developed from wilderness living * Basic foraging and navigation abilities', 'Bottar speaks rarely and quietly, using simple, direct language when he must communicate. His sparse vocabulary reflects his limited interaction with settled society, though he likely knows common Nordic terms and expressions.', '* Survive and thrive in Skyrim''s wilderness alongside his friend Sond * Continue exploring and discovering new locations throughout the province * Perhaps find a permanent home or reunite with family members if they still exist');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('frodnar', 'Frodnar is a mischievous young Nord boy living in Riverwood who delights in playing pranks and dreams of following in his uncle Ralof''s footsteps as a Stormcloak soldier. Despite his playful nature, he shows early signs of strong Nord values and political awareness unusual for his age, shaped by his family''s pro-Stormcloak stance and his admiration for his warrior uncle.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Riverwood, Frodnar grew up in a politically conscious household as the son of Gerdur, the village leader, and Hod, the mill owner. His early years were heavily influenced by visits from his uncle Ralof, whose tales of adventure and combat with the Stormcloaks helped shape Frodnar''s worldview and aspirations. His privileged position as the son of Riverwood''s leading family has given him a sense of confidence and security that manifests in his bold pranking behavior.', 'Frodnar exhibits a complex mix of childish mischief and premature political awareness, often alternating between playful pranks and serious discussions about the civil war. He displays remarkable confidence for his age, bordering on arrogance, and shows little remorse for his pranks despite others'' complaints. Despite his troublemaking nature, he harbors genuine admiration for the Stormcloak cause and demonstrates loyalty to his family and their values.', 'A typical Nord child with the characteristic fair complexion common to his race. He has the sturdy build typical of Nord children, though still clearly in his developmental years. His face often carries a mischievous grin, reflecting his playful nature.', '* Gerdur - Mother and village leader, who tries to instill responsibility in him * Hod - Father and mill owner, who shows patience with his antics * Ralof - Uncle and Stormcloak soldier, whom he deeply admires and wishes to emulate * Dorthe - Best friend and frequent target of his pranks, daughter of the local blacksmith * Stump - His loyal dog and constant companion * Hadvar - Views him with suspicion due to Imperial allegiance', 'As a child, Frodnar has no formal occupation, though he is expected to eventually take over his parents'' mill. He occasionally helps at the mill when required, though he resents being made to work, declaring that he ''ain''t nobody''s slave.'' His main activities revolve around playing with his dog Stump and devising new pranks.', '* Natural leadership qualities inherited from his mother, though currently expressed through organizing pranks * Basic understanding of mill operations from observing his parents * Skilled at devising and executing elaborate pranks * Developing combat skills through play-fighting and dagger practice * Shows aptitude for stealth when setting up his pranks', 'Frodnar speaks with the direct, unfiltered honesty of youth, often making bold declarations and threats of pranks. His vocabulary switches between childish playfulness and attempts at adult-like seriousness when discussing the war or Stormcloaks.', '* Join the Stormcloak rebellion when he comes of age * Become a great warrior like his uncle Ralof * Perfect his pranking abilities and become known as Riverwood''s greatest trickster * Eventually take over the family mill, though he currently resists this destiny * Prove himself worthy of his family''s prominent position in Riverwood');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('frothar', 'Frothar is the eldest son of Jarl Balgruuf the Greater, representing a more mature and levelheaded presence among the children of Dragonsreach. Unlike his siblings, he demonstrates a keen interest in warfare and leadership while maintaining a respectful demeanor that befits his position as the jarl''s heir apparent.', 'nord, noble, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in the prestigious halls of Dragonsreach, Frothar has grown up witnessing the politics and responsibilities of rulership through his father''s example. Though his mother''s identity and fate remain unknown, he has been groomed from an early age to understand the duties of leadership and the martial traditions of Nord culture.', 'Frothar exhibits a mature and practical mindset unusual for his age, showing genuine interest in warfare and governance while maintaining appropriate respect for authority. Unlike his more petulant siblings, he demonstrates patience and understanding of his current limitations, though he eagerly anticipates growing into a warrior role. His criticism of his sister Dagny''s behavior reveals both his sense of responsibility and awareness of proper noble conduct.', 'As a young Nord boy, Frothar possesses the characteristic sturdy build of his race, though still in his childhood years. He likely shares some of his father''s features, including the typical Nord fair complexion and light hair common among his people.', '* Jarl Balgruuf the Greater - His father and role model, whom he seeks to emulate * Dagny - Younger sister with whom he has a strained relationship due to her spoiled nature * Nelkir - Younger brother who shares the castle but seems distant * Proventus Avenicci - The steward who likely assists in his education * Irileth - The housecarl who possibly provides basic combat instruction', 'As the eldest son of Jarl Balgruuf, Frothar''s primary role is that of heir and future leader of Whiterun Hold. His current duties likely include studying governance, military strategy, and Nord traditions in preparation for his future responsibilities.', '* Basic combat training, primarily focusing on unarmed fighting as he''s deemed too young for weapons * Developing understanding of politics and leadership through observation of his father * Knowledge of Nordic history and traditions befitting a jarl''s heir * Social skills appropriate for a future leader', 'Frothar speaks with the directness characteristic of Nords, but maintains a respectful and proper tone befitting his noble upbringing. His dialogue reflects both youthful enthusiasm and a growing awareness of formal speech patterns appropriate for his station.', '* Prove himself worthy of joining the war when he comes of age * Learn combat skills and master the art of warfare * Live up to his father''s legacy and prepare himself for future leadership * Earn glory and honor in battle as befits a true Nord warrior');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gralnach', 'Gralnach is a resilient young Nord boy who helps run Heartwood Mill alongside his mother Grosta following his father''s mysterious disappearance. Despite his youth, he displays remarkable maturity and determination, balancing his responsibilities at the mill with his deep desire to understand the truth about his father''s fate.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Leifnarr and Grosta, Gralnach grew up at Heartwood Mill learning the family trade. His life changed dramatically when his father disappeared, initially believed to have abandoned the family but later discovered to have died heroically. This early loss forced him to mature quickly, taking on mill responsibilities while still processing his grief.', 'Gralnach exhibits a unique blend of childhood innocence and forced maturity, often masking his emotional vulnerability with displays of bravado and claims of toughness. He shows remarkable resilience and determination for his age, though his persistent curiosity about his father reveals his deeper emotional needs. Despite challenging circumstances, he maintains a strong sense of duty and family loyalty.', 'As a Nord child, Gralnach possesses the characteristic fair features of his race, though his work at the mill has given him a sturdy build unusual for his age. His appearance reflects his dual nature - both a child and a young worker - with hands already showing early calluses from mill work.', '* Grosta - His mother and primary caregiver, with whom he shares a complex but loving relationship * Leifnarr - His deceased father, whom he deeply admires and seeks to understand better * Mill Workers - Maintains casual relationships with various traders and lumber workers who visit the mill', 'Though technically too young for full employment, Gralnach serves as an apprentice millworker at Heartwood Mill, learning the trade from his mother. He assists with various tasks including tree selection, basic cutting work, and general mill maintenance.', '* Basic knowledge of lumber work and tree selection * Developing physical strength from mill work * Elementary survival skills necessary for life near the wilderness * Basic understanding of mill operations and maintenance', 'Gralnach speaks with a mix of childlike enthusiasm and attempted maturity, often trying to sound more grown-up than he is. His dialogue alternates between confident assertions about his capabilities and more vulnerable moments when discussing his father.', '* Master the millwork trade to eventually take over Heartwood Mill * Preserve and honor his father''s memory * Prove himself capable of protecting and maintaining the mill * Support his mother while maintaining hope for a better future');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('gimvar_cruel-sea', 'Grimvar Cruel-Sea is a young Nord boy from a wealthy Windhelm family who dreams of becoming a legendary warrior despite his father''s wishes for him to follow the family''s maritime tradition. His curious and ambitious nature, coupled with his unusual tolerance in the racially divided city of Windhelm, marks him as a unique child whose interests span from dragon-slaying to the darker mysteries of the Black Sacrament.', 'nord, warrior, sailor, eastmarch', '', '', '', '', 'Born into the wealthy and influential Cruel-Sea clan of Windhelm, Grimvar has enjoyed a privileged upbringing in the ancient city of Ysgramor. Despite his family''s focus on maritime trade and farming, he has developed a strong fascination with warriors and combat, possibly influenced by the stories of ancient Nord heroes that permeate Windhelm''s culture. His daily care under Idesa Sadri, a Dark Elf, has given him a more tolerant worldview than many of his Nord peers.', 'Grimvar exhibits a bold and adventurous spirit, often speaking of his desires to become a warrior and fight dragons, showing an ambitious nature unusual for his age. He demonstrates remarkable emotional maturity through his lack of racial prejudice, treating his Dark Elf caretaker and others with respect despite living in a city known for its racial tensions. His curiosity about the Black Sacrament reveals a darker fascination with the mysterious and forbidden.', 'As a young Nord boy, Grimvar has the characteristic sturdy build of his race, though still with the gangly limbs of childhood. He likely has the fair skin common to Nords, with the strong facial features that mark the people of Windhelm.', '* Torsten Cruel-Sea - Father, wealthy merchant who wishes him to become a sailor * Hillevi Cruel-Sea - Mother, who supports his upbringing * Idesa Sadri - Dark Elf caretaker who spends most time with him * Aventus Aretino - Subject of fascination due to Black Sacrament rumors * Windhelm''s youth - Peer group with whom he interacts daily', 'As a child of nobility, Grimvar''s current occupation consists of education and preparation for his future role in Windhelm society. He spends his days under the care of Idesa Sadri, learning both practical skills and formal education befitting his family''s status.', '* Basic education and literacy as expected of a noble''s son * Developing understanding of maritime trade from family teachings * Budding interest in combat and warrior techniques * Social skills that transcend typical racial boundaries of Windhelm', 'Grimvar speaks with the direct and proud manner common to Nord children, but his vocabulary reveals his educated upbringing. His dialogue often focuses on his aspirations and curiosities, showing both childlike wonder and surprising maturity.', '* Become a renowned warrior capable of fighting dragons and other legendary threats * Forge his own path distinct from his father''s maritime ambitions * Uncover the mysteries surrounding the Black Sacrament and Aventus Aretino * Gain recognition and respect beyond his family''s mercantile reputation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('haming', 'Haming is a resilient young Nord boy who survived the devastating dragon attack on Helgen that claimed his parents'' lives. Despite his tragic past, he maintains a brave and curious spirit while living with his grandfather Froki, embodying the strength and determination characteristic of Nord children.', 'nord, peasant, falkreath, rift', '', '', '', '', 'Born in Helgen to Torolf and Matlara, Haming lived a peaceful life until age eleven when Alduin''s attack destroyed his hometown and killed his parents. He survived thanks to the quick actions of his father and Imperial soldier Hadvar, after which he relocated to Froki''s Shack to live with his grandfather, a seasoned hunter and warrior.', 'Despite his youth, Haming displays remarkable resilience and emotional strength in the face of profound loss. He maintains a curious and adventurous spirit typical of Nord children, combined with an underlying maturity born from tragedy. While obedient to authority figures, he still harbors a warrior''s spirit and desire to prove himself.', 'Haming is a typical Nord child with the characteristic sturdy build of his race, though still showing the gangly nature of pre-adolescence. He has the fair complexion common to Nords, with features that hint at both his father''s rugged appearance and his mother''s gentler aspects.', '* Froki Whetted-Blade - Grandfather and current guardian, teaching him hunting and survival skills * Torolf - Deceased father who sacrificed himself to save Haming during the Helgen attack * Matlara - Deceased mother who perished in Helgen * Hadvar - Imperial soldier who helped ensure his survival during the dragon attack', 'As a child, Haming assists his grandfather with basic hunting and survival tasks around Froki''s Shack. He is learning the ways of hunting and wilderness survival from his grandfather, though he''s not yet allowed to hunt independently.', '* Basic hunting knowledge learned from his grandfather Froki * Survival skills necessary for living in the wilderness * Growing proficiency with an iron dagger * Natural resilience and adaptability to harsh circumstances', 'Haming speaks with the direct, sometimes boastful manner typical of Nord children, though his dialogue occasionally reveals a maturity beyond his years when discussing his past. His speech patterns reflect both childlike enthusiasm and the sobering effects of his experiences.', '* Master hunting skills to prove himself worthy of his grandfather''s teachings * Become strong enough to eventually hunt and kill a dragon on his own * Honor his parents'' memory by growing into a capable warrior * Learn to survive independently in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hroar', 'Hroar is a resilient young Nord orphan living at Honorhall Orphanage who maintains remarkable optimism despite his harsh circumstances. Named after a lion''s roar by his late mother, he embodies a child''s determination to find belonging and strength in a world that has shown him little kindness.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a Nord mother who passed away when he was young, Hroar ended up at Honorhall Orphanage in Riften. His mother instilled pride in him by naming him after a lion''s roar, a legacy he clings to as one of his few connections to his family history. He has spent his formative years under the cruel supervision of Grelod the Kind, forming close bonds with his fellow orphans while enduring daily mistreatment.', 'Despite his harsh upbringing, Hroar maintains a remarkably resilient and optimistic disposition. He shows pride in his unique name and demonstrates a yearning to embody the strength and courage of a lion. Though generally good-natured, he harbors a darker side that welcomes the idea of Grelod''s assassination, revealing how deeply her cruelty has affected him.', 'A young Nord boy with the typical hardy Nordic features, though somewhat thin from the orphanage''s restricted meals. Like most Nord children, he likely has fair skin and light hair, with a frame that shows potential for the strong build characteristic of his race.', '* Grelod the Kind - Abusive caretaker whom he fears and resents * Constance Michel - Kind caretaker who sometimes sneaks him extra food * Aventus Aretino - Former fellow orphan he supports in seeking Grelod''s death * Samuel, Runa, and Francois - Fellow orphans and closest friends * Deceased Mother - Cherished memory and source of pride regarding his name', 'As a child in Honorhall Orphanage, Hroar''s daily duties consist of completing chores assigned by Grelod and maintaining the orphanage. He follows a strict schedule of meals, playtime, and work, typical of institutionalized orphans in Skyrim.', '* Basic domestic skills learned from orphanage chores * Social adaptability developed from surviving in a harsh environment * Physical resilience from enduring limited meals and harsh conditions * Ability to find moments of joy and play despite difficult circumstances', 'Hroar speaks with the direct honesty of a child, often proudly referencing his name and its meaning. His manner of speech alternates between youthful enthusiasm and a more subdued tone when discussing life at the orphanage.', '* Find a loving adoptive family and prove himself as ''the best son ever'' * Grow strong like the lion his name represents * Escape the cruel environment of Honorhall Orphanage * Honor his mother''s memory by living up to the strength his name implies');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('joric', 'Joric is a young Nord boy blessed - or perhaps cursed - with inherited supernatural abilities that allow him to experience prophetic visions and temporal displacement, much like his mother Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone. Despite his young age, he struggles with these overwhelming abilities while trying to maintain a semblance of normal childhood in Morthal, often questioning his own sanity and place in reality.', 'nord, noble, hjaalmarch', '', '', '', '', 'Born into the ruling family of Hjaalmarch, Joric inherited the gift of supernatural sight that runs in his bloodline. From an early age, he began experiencing disturbing visions and episodes of apparent dissociation, leading some townsfolk to question his mental state. His condition has made it difficult for him to develop normal childhood relationships or fully engage with the world around him.', 'Joric is a deeply introspective and troubled child who constantly questions his own perception of reality. Despite his supernatural burden, he maintains a curious nature and shows remarkable insight when lucid. His personality fluctuates between periods of clarity and confusion, often expressing both wisdom beyond his years and childlike vulnerability.', 'Joric is a young Nord boy with the characteristic fair features of his race. His face often bears a distant, dreamy expression that betrays his supernatural experiences. Despite his noble birth, his physical appearance is that of a typical Nord child, though perhaps slightly more pale and tired-looking than most children his age.', '* Idgrod Ravencrone (Mother) - Shares his gift of supernatural sight and understands his struggles * Aslfur (Father) - Protective and concerned for his well-being * Idgrod the Younger (Sister) - Fellow gifted family member who helps watch over him * Gorm - Household member who doubts his sanity * Falion - Mysterious figure who Joric seems to have supernatural insights about', 'As the son of Jarl Idgrod Ravencrone, Joric holds no formal occupation but is part of Morthal''s ruling family. His primary focus is dealing with his supernatural experiences while attempting to maintain some semblance of a normal childhood.', '* Natural gift of prophetic sight and supernatural perception * Ability to experience temporal displacement or astral projection * Unusual insight into magical occurrences and individuals * Enhanced sensitivity to supernatural phenomena', 'Joric speaks in cryptic, often disjointed sentences that reflect his disconnection from normal reality. His dialogue alternates between childlike confusion and eerily profound observations, frequently questioning his own experiences and sanity.', '* Learn to control and understand his supernatural abilities * Find a way to distinguish between visions and reality * Gain acceptance from those who doubt his sanity * Navigate his role as part of Morthal''s ruling family despite his condition');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('knud_repeated', 'Knud is a young Nord boy living and working on Katla''s Farm near Solitude, representing the next generation of Skyrim''s hardy farming folk. Despite his youth, he shows dedication to farm life while maintaining childlike wonder and imagination, balancing his duties with playful adventures around the farmstead.', 'nord, peasant, haafingar', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Katla and Snilling, Knud has spent his entire young life on the family farm near Solitude, learning the ways of agricultural life from his earliest days. Though his father believes he lacks aptitude for reading, Knud has developed a strong work ethic and practical knowledge of farming through hands-on experience. His upbringing in the shadow of Solitude''s walls has given him exposure to both rural farm life and glimpses of the grand city''s military presence, influencing his imaginative play as a soldier.', 'Cheerful and industrious, Knud approaches his farm duties with enthusiasm while maintaining the innocent excitement typical of children his age. He demonstrates strong respect for authority and guests, reflecting his parents'' careful upbringing and Nord values. Despite his modest circumstances, he shows contentment with farm life and finds joy in both work and play, often incorporating imagination into his daily routines.', 'A typical Nord child with the sturdy build common to his race, showing early signs of the physical resilience needed for farm work. His features reflect his Nordic heritage, with fair skin and the characteristic robust constitution of his people.', '* Katla - Mother and farm owner, who guides him in learning farm management * Snilling - Father who oversees his development, though concerned about his reading abilities * Farm Animals - Shows particular attachment to the goats he helps tend * Passing Travelers - Maintains polite, friendly interactions with visitors to the farm', 'As a child farmhand, Knud assists with various agricultural tasks appropriate for his age and ability. His primary responsibilities include tending to the goats and performing basic farm chores, all while learning the skills necessary to potentially take over the family farm one day.', '* Basic animal husbandry, particularly with goats * Fundamental farming techniques suitable for a child * Growing knowledge of farm operations and maintenance * Developing physical stamina for farm work * Creative play and imagination, especially in military role-play', 'Speaks with the direct, simple vocabulary typical of a Nord child, often expressing enthusiasm through exclamations and eager questions. His manner of speech reflects both his youth and the practical nature of farm life, peppered with references to his daily activities and imaginative games.', '* Learn all aspects of farming to help his family maintain their livelihood * Improve his abilities with farm work and animal care * Perhaps one day become a soldier, as suggested by his playful imagination * Make his parents proud through hard work and good behavior');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('lars_battle-born', 'Lars Battle-Born is a young Nord boy from the prestigious Battle-Born clan who struggles with being bullied and feeling inadequate in Whiterun''s warrior culture. Despite coming from a prominent family known for their strength and martial prowess, Lars represents a more sensitive soul who struggles with living up to his family''s legacy.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born into the wealthy and influential Battle-Born family of Whiterun, Lars was raised in relative privilege but failed to develop the typical Nordic warrior traits his family values. His early childhood experiences of being unable to defend himself against bullying, particularly from Braith, have shaped his self-image and created a rift between his natural disposition and his family''s expectations.', 'Lars is timid, sensitive, and deeply insecure about his perceived weakness in a culture that values strength and combat prowess. He shows signs of intelligence and compassion but struggles with anxiety and fear, particularly in confrontational situations. Despite his family''s disappointment, he maintains a gentle nature and seeks ways to cope with his challenges through avoidance rather than confrontation.', 'A young Nord boy with the characteristic fair features of his race, likely with the blonde hair common to many Nords. He has a smaller, less robust build compared to other Nord children his age, contributing to his physical insecurities.', '* Alfhild Battle-Born - Mother who struggles to understand her sensitive son * Idolaf Battle-Born - Father who shows disappointment in Lars''s lack of warrior spirit * Bergritte Battle-Born - Grandmother who shows him understanding and protection * Braith - Primary tormentor and source of his daily anxiety * Mila Valentia - Former playmate mentioned in his dialogue about past adventures', 'As a child of the Battle-Born clan, Lars''s primary role is to learn and prepare to eventually take his place as a member of this prestigious family. He spends his days around Whiterun, typically avoiding confrontation and seeking safe spaces.', '* Basic literacy and education befitting a noble family''s child * Knowledge of Whiterun''s layout and hidden spots for avoiding bullies * Climbing abilities (mentioned in dialogue about climbing Dragonsreach) * Some experience in sneaking, primarily used to avoid confrontation', 'Lars speaks with a timid, hesitant manner, often expressing self-doubt and anxiety in his words. His vocabulary reflects his upper-class upbringing, but his delivery is marked by uncertainty and a lack of confidence.', '* Overcome his fears and develop the courage to stand up for himself * Gain his family''s approval and respect despite his non-warrior nature * Find a way to be accepted for who he is rather than who others expect him to be * Escape the constant bullying from Braith');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nelkir', 'Nelkir is the troubled and embittered youngest son of Jarl Balgruuf the Greater, harboring dark secrets and a mysterious connection to the Whispering Lady. Born of a different mother than his siblings, he struggles with feelings of alienation and resentment while maintaining an unusually perceptive understanding of the political intrigue surrounding his father''s court.', 'nord, noble, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born as the illegitimate son of Jarl Balgruuf the Greater, Nelkir''s early life was marked by the absence of his birth mother and the stigma of being a bastard child in the Jarl''s household. His isolation and tendency to explore the forgotten corners of Dragonsreach led him to discover the Whispering Lady, who began sharing dark secrets with him and possibly influencing his psychological development.', 'Deeply cynical and distrustful, Nelkir exhibits emotional maturity beyond his years, coupled with a disturbing tendency toward dark thoughts and violent fantasies. His bitter worldview and sharp tongue mask deep emotional wounds, while his secretive nature and keen observational skills make him uniquely aware of the political undercurrents in Whiterun.', 'A Nord child with the characteristic features of his father''s bloodline, though perhaps bearing some physical traits of his unknown mother. His face often carries a scowl or suspicious expression, making him appear older than his actual years.', '* Jarl Balgruuf the Greater - His father, toward whom he harbors intense resentment and violent thoughts * Frothar and Dagny - Half-siblings who share his father but not his mother * The Whispering Lady - Mysterious entity who shares secrets with him and possibly manipulates him * Proventus Avenicci - The Jarl''s steward, whom Nelkir likely views with suspicion * Unknown Mother - Absent from his life, contributing to his sense of abandonment', 'As the Jarl''s son, Nelkir holds a position of privilege in Whiterun''s court, though he shows little interest in the responsibilities or expectations that come with his station. His true ''occupation'' seems to be that of a secret-keeper and observer, spending much time exploring hidden areas of Dragonsreach and eavesdropping on conversations.', '* Exceptional ability to discover and keep secrets * Advanced understanding of political intrigue for his age * Skilled at moving quietly and eavesdropping * Natural talent for observation and gathering information * Understanding of Dragonsreach''s hidden passages and architectural secrets', 'Nelkir speaks with a cynical, mature vocabulary unusual for a child his age, often employing sarcasm and dark humor. His manner of speech is direct and cutting, showing little regard for social niceties or respect for authority.', '* Uncover more secrets about his father and the court of Whiterun * Learn the truth about his mother''s identity and whereabouts * Continue his relationship with the Whispering Lady * Perhaps secretly wishes to gain his father''s genuine attention and acknowledgment * Possibly harbors desires for revenge or validation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('skuli', 'Skuli is a remarkably mature young Nord boy who serves as the de facto co-manager of the Old Hroldan Inn alongside his mother Eydis. Despite his tender age, he demonstrates exceptional responsibility and business acumen, handling adult duties while harboring unspoken concerns about his missing father''s true fate.', 'nord, innkeeper, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised at the Old Hroldan Inn in the dangerous reaches of the Reach, Skuli learned the hospitality trade from an early age under his mother''s guidance. His father''s unexplained disappearance, though not directly acknowledged to him, has forced him to take on adult responsibilities prematurely, shaping him into a serious and capable child far beyond his years.', 'Skuli exhibits a precocious maturity and no-nonsense attitude that belies his youth, approaching inn management with the seriousness of a seasoned proprietor. Though stern when enforcing rules or defending his capabilities, he maintains an underlying vulnerability about his father''s absence, masked by his professional demeanor and strong work ethic.', 'A young Nord boy with the characteristic hardy build of his race, though still with the slight frame of childhood. His features show signs of premature aging from stress and responsibility, with eyes that carry wisdom beyond their years.', '* Eydis - His mother and inn proprietor, whom he helps run the establishment * Missing Father - Whereabouts unknown, though Skuli suspects his mother''s explanations aren''t entirely truthful * Inn Patrons - Maintains professional relationships despite his youth, commanding respect through his mature demeanor', 'Junior innkeeper at the Old Hroldan Inn, where he performs virtually all duties expected of an adult proprietor. His responsibilities include serving food and drinks, maintaining rooms, handling customer relations, and enforcing inn rules and policies.', '* Proficient in all aspects of inn management despite his young age * Capable of maintaining order among adult patrons through stern authority * Experienced in food service and room maintenance * Advanced social skills for handling difficult customers professionally', 'Speaks with a maturity and authority unusual for a child, often using direct and professional language typical of adult innkeepers. His tone can be stern when necessary, though his youth occasionally shows through in moments of vulnerability.', '* Maintain the inn''s reputation and success alongside his mother * Discover the truth about his father''s disappearance while maintaining his stoic facade * Continue developing his innkeeping skills to become a full-fledged proprietor');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('smaref_ice-blade', 'Smaref Ice-Blade is the young heir to a once-powerful Nord clan, living in ignorance of his noble heritage and family tragedy in Riften. His life represents the intersection of High Rock politics and Nord tradition, unknowingly carrying the weight of his clan''s future while maintaining the innocent perspective of a child.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', '', '', 'Born to the prestigious Clan Ice-Blade, Smaref''s early life was marked by tragedy when his mother was assassinated in a political plot orchestrated by Erikur and Gisli. The clan''s lands near Jehanna in High Rock were seized through manipulation, and Smaref was relocated to Riften to live in comfortable obscurity. His true identity and inheritance were kept hidden from him until his uncle Pjofr''s arrival to reclaim their family''s honor.', 'Despite his noble heritage, Smaref displays the typical characteristics of a sheltered child, maintaining an innocent and carefree demeanor unaffected by the political machinations surrounding him. He shows natural curiosity about his environment and the people of Riften, though his privileged upbringing is evident in his mannerisms and expectations. His resilience in the face of unconscious adversity suggests an inherent strength of character typical of Nord bloodlines.', 'Smaref has the characteristic Nordic features of his bloodline, with fair skin and light hair typical of his race. As a child, he possesses a sturdy build common to Nord children, though still carrying the softness of youth. His bearing, even in childhood, hints at his noble lineage through naturally good posture and proud stance.', '* Pjofr Ice-Blade - Uncle and protector who comes to restore his birthright * Unknown Mother - Assassinated as part of political intrigue * Erikur and Gisli - Hidden enemies responsible for his family''s downfall * Riften Caretakers - Those assigned to maintain his comfortable lifestyle while in hiding', 'As a child, Smaref has no formal occupation, though he is unknowingly preparing for his future role as the heir of Clan Ice-Blade. His daily life in Riften consists primarily of protected activities suitable for a child of his status, though the true purpose of his presence there remains hidden from him.', '* Basic education typical of noble children * Natural leadership qualities inherited from his bloodline * Social skills developed through privileged upbringing * Emerging understanding of Nord traditions and customs', 'Smaref speaks with the innocent directness of a child, though his vocabulary and diction reflect his noble upbringing. His manner of speech carries subtle hints of both High Rock refinement and Nordic straightforwardness.', '* Return to High Rock with his uncle to reclaim his birthright * Learn about his family''s history and heritage * Restore honor to Clan Ice-Blade * Grow into his role as the future leader of his clan');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sond', 'Sond is a resourceful young Nord child who has carved out a unique entrepreneurial niche by guiding travelers to Dwemer ruins and selling scavenged goods. Despite his youth, he demonstrates remarkable survival instincts and business acumen, having learned to navigate both the physical dangers of Skyrim''s wilderness and the art of negotiation with passing adventurers.', 'nord, peasant, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to poor farmers in the wilds of Skyrim, Sond learned early on to fend for himself through scavenging and trading. After befriending Bottar, the two children began exploring the wilderness together, eventually discovering the Deep Folk Crossing and recognizing its value as a source of income. Their knowledge of local Dwemer ruins has become their primary means of survival, though the full story of how they came to live so independently remains a mystery.', 'Sond exhibits a shrewd and opportunistic nature tempered by childlike enthusiasm and adaptability. While he attempts to project confidence in his dealings with travelers, his quick capitulation to threats reveals his underlying vulnerability and survival instincts. He shows remarkable resilience and ingenuity for his age, having adapted to life in the wilderness through wit and resourcefulness.', 'A typical Nord child with the characteristic fair complexion and hardy build of his race. His face shows signs of outdoor living, with wind-chapped cheeks and minor scrapes from his wilderness adventures. Despite the challenging lifestyle, he maintains the robust health typical of Nord children.', '* Bottar - Close friend and exploration companion who shares his entrepreneurial ventures * Local Traders - Occasional business relationships when selling scavenged goods * Passing Adventurers - Temporary commercial relationships as potential customers * Unknown Parents - Absent or deceased, leaving Sond to fend for himself', 'Sond operates as an informal guide and trader, specializing in directing travelers to Dwemer ruins while maintaining a small side business selling scavenged items. His entrepreneurial activities, though modest, demonstrate remarkable initiative for a child living in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness.', '* Skilled at navigation and pathfinding in the wilderness * Basic trading and negotiation abilities * Survival skills including scavenging and avoiding dangerous wildlife * Knowledge of local Dwemer ruins and their locations * Basic stealth skills for avoiding threats', 'Sond speaks with a mix of youthful excitement and attempted business formality, often using simple but direct language. His tone shifts between playful confidence when making sales pitches and submissive compliance when faced with intimidation.', '* Maintain a successful trading operation with passing adventurers * Expand his knowledge of valuable locations to sell as waypoints * Survive and thrive independently in Skyrim''s wilderness * Build a more stable life through his entrepreneurial ventures');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vikmund', 'Vikmund is a young Nord child in Morthal struggling with the mysterious disappearance of his mother, clinging to hope despite his father''s attempts to help him accept reality. His daily life is marked by a mix of childhood normalcy and deep emotional yearning, as he maintains friendships while processing his profound sense of loss.', 'nord, peasant, hjaalmarch', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Morthal, Vikmund lived a relatively peaceful life with his parents until his mother''s unexplained disappearance. The circumstances of her departure remain unclear to him, though his father Thonnir seems to know more than he reveals. The loss has fundamentally shaped Vikmund''s childhood and his understanding of family.', 'Vikmund displays a sensitive and hopeful nature, often refusing to accept the finality of his mother''s absence despite evidence to the contrary. He shows resilience in maintaining daily routines and friendships while carrying this emotional burden. His persistent optimism about his mother''s return reveals both childlike innocence and a deep-seated need for closure.', 'A typical Nord child with the characteristic fair complexion common to his race. His features reflect his youth and innocence, though his eyes often carry a trace of melancholy unusual for a child his age.', '* Thonnir - His father who struggles to help him accept his mother''s absence * Agni - Close childhood friend who provides companionship and emotional support * Lami - Adult figure he visits regularly at the Thaumaturgist''s Hut * Mother (Missing) - Source of emotional turmoil and constant longing', 'As a child in Morthal, Vikmund''s main activities revolve around play, social interactions, and processing his personal loss. He maintains a daily routine of visiting specific locations and people in town, which helps provide structure to his life.', '* Basic understanding of Nordic customs and traditions * Ability to maintain friendships despite emotional difficulties * Developing social skills typical of Nord children * Knowledge of Morthal''s layout and community', 'Vikmund speaks with the directness typical of Nord children, though his words often carry emotional weight beyond his years. His dialogue frequently returns to the subject of his mother, revealing both hope and underlying sadness.', '* Find out what truly happened to his mother * Maintain hope for his mother''s eventual return * Navigate daily life while processing his loss * Strengthen his friendship with Agni');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('adara', 'Adara is a bright and ambitious Redguard child in Markarth who serves as an apprentice silversmith under her father Endon''s tutelage. Despite her young age, she shows remarkable talent in metalworking and takes pride in carrying on her family''s craft traditions while managing occasional duties at her mother''s jewelry stall.', 'redguard, peasant, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born into a family of skilled Redguard silversmiths in Markarth, Adara grew up watching her parents craft fine jewelry and silverwork. Her early childhood was marked by close family bonds until her older brother Cade left to join the Stormcloaks, creating a bittersweet dynamic in their household as they balance pride in their craft with worry for their absent son.', 'Energetic and enthusiastic, Adara approaches her apprenticeship with infectious excitement and natural curiosity. She demonstrates remarkable maturity in handling both crafting responsibilities and merchant duties, though her childlike exuberance occasionally shows through in her inability to contain her excitement. Despite her generally cheerful demeanor, she harbors a deep longing for her brother''s return.', 'A young Redguard girl with the characteristic dark skin and athletic build of her race. Her hands, though small, already show the developing calluses of a metalworker, and she carries herself with the natural grace common to Redguard children.', '* Endon - Beloved father and mentor who teaches her the art of silversmithing * Kerah - Caring mother whose merchant stall she helps manage * Cade - Older brother fighting with the Stormcloaks, whom she misses dearly * Markarth Guards - Generally protective of her as a known merchant''s child * Silver-Blood Family - Business acquaintances of her family', 'Adara serves as both an apprentice silversmith under her father''s guidance and occasional merchant when covering her mother''s jewelry stall. Though too young to conduct actual trades, she takes pride in attracting customers and learning the family business.', '* Developing proficiency in silversmithing and metalworking * Basic merchant and salesmanship abilities * Growing knowledge of jewelry crafting techniques * Natural talent for metal manipulation noted by her father', 'Speaks with childlike enthusiasm and pride about her craft, occasionally stumbling over merchant phrases when manning the stall. Her speech patterns reflect both her youth and her attempt to sound professional like her parents.', '* Master the art of silversmithing and become as skilled as her parents * Make her family proud through dedication to their craft * See her brother Cade return safely from war * Eventually run her own successful jewelry business in Markarth');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('braith', 'Braith is a troubled young Redguard girl living in Whiterun who masks her deep emotional pain through aggressive behavior and bullying. Behind her tough exterior lies a lonely child desperately seeking attention from her distracted parents, particularly her mother Saffir, while struggling to process her feelings of abandonment and neglect.', 'redguard, peasant, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Amren and Saffir in Whiterun, Braith grew up in an emotionally distant household where her father obsessed over finding his lost family sword and her mother remained constantly absorbed in books. The lack of parental attention and guidance during her formative years led her to develop maladaptive coping mechanisms, primarily expressed through bullying other children, especially Lars Battle-Born.', 'Braith presents a fierce and confrontational exterior, quick to threaten violence and assert dominance over others as a way to feel in control. Beneath this aggressive facade lies a deeply hurt and lonely child who yearns for parental love and validation, particularly from her mother. Her bullying behavior serves as both a cry for attention and a misguided attempt to process her emotional neglect.', 'As a young Redguard girl, Braith has the characteristic dark skin and strong features of her race. She appears physically fit and athletic from her daily activities around Whiterun, with an energetic bearing that matches her assertive personality.', '* Amren - Father who is emotionally distant, preoccupied with finding his lost sword * Saffir - Mother who neglects her in favor of reading books * Lars Battle-Born - Primary target of her bullying, secretly harbors a crush on him * Mila Valentia - Fellow child of Whiterun, occasional playmate * Other Whiterun Children - Generally antagonistic relationships due to her bullying behavior', 'As a child in Whiterun, Braith has no formal occupation but spends her days playing in the streets and interacting with other children. Her self-appointed role as the local bully gives her a notorious reputation among the city''s younger residents.', '* Intimidation tactics and threatening behavior * Physical combat, though mainly limited to childhood scuffles * Survival skills developed from spending much time fending for herself * Social manipulation, particularly in extracting money or compliance from other children', 'Braith speaks with an aggressive, confrontational tone that often includes threats and bravado. Her vocabulary and manner of speech are typical of a child trying to sound tough and intimidating, frequently challenging others with phrases like ''Boys, girls, dogs, elders - there''s nobody I won''t fight!''', '* Gain attention and acknowledgment from her parents, especially her mother * Assert control over her environment through dominance of other children * Secretly wishes to develop a closer relationship with Lars Battle-Born * Find ways to cope with her feelings of abandonment and loneliness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('alesan', 'Alesan is a resilient young Redguard orphan who has carved out a humble living in the harsh environment of Dawnstar by serving as a courier between the Windpeak Inn and local miners. Despite his young age, he demonstrates remarkable responsibility and work ethic, having adapted to survive on his own after losing his father to illness.', 'redguard, peasant, pale', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a Redguard sailor father who frequently traveled the northern waters, Alesan spent his early years at sea learning the ways of maritime life. During his father''s last voyage, illness struck, forcing them to dock at Dawnstar where they were abandoned by the crew. After his father''s death, Alesan found himself alone in the unfamiliar Nordic city, where he had to quickly learn to survive through whatever work he could find.', 'Alesan exhibits a strong sense of responsibility and work ethic unusual for his age, likely developed as a survival mechanism after being orphaned. He maintains a focused, almost anxious demeanor while working, reflecting his fear of losing his tenuous position in Dawnstar society. Despite his hardships, he shows remarkable resilience and adaptability, having developed a practical approach to life rather than succumbing to despair.', 'As a young Redguard boy, Alesan has the characteristic dark skin and sturdy build of his race, though somewhat lean from his modest lifestyle. His constant running through Dawnstar has given him an athletic physique despite his youth. His features show signs of weathering from exposure to Dawnstar''s harsh climate.', '* Thoring - Innkeeper who allows him to sleep by the fire, showing him basic kindness * Karita - Inn worker who provides him with food to deliver * Local Miners (Gjak, Karl, Lond, Borgny) - Regular customers of his delivery service * Deceased Father - Former sailor who raised him until falling ill in Dawnstar', 'Alesan works as a courier and general helper in Dawnstar, primarily running food and supplies from the Windpeak Inn to the miners at Quicksilver and Iron-Breaker Mines. He supplements this income by performing additional tasks like feeding chickens at the inn, demonstrating his willingness to take on any work available.', '* Experienced runner with excellent stamina and knowledge of Dawnstar''s layout * Basic understanding of mining operations and supply logistics * Survival skills developed from living on his own * Rudimentary business sense from managing his delivery service', 'Alesan speaks in short, hurried phrases while working, often apologizing for rushing past people. His manner of speech reflects his constant state of being busy and his awareness that his survival depends on maintaining his reputation for reliability.', '* Secure a more stable living situation beyond sleeping at the inn * Maintain and possibly expand his delivery service to ensure steady income * Find a real home and family to belong to * Honor his father''s memory by continuing to work hard and survive');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kayd', 'Kayd is a spirited young Redguard boy living in Solitude who helps at his mother''s shop while idolizing his father''s strength and prowess. As the child of a merchant and blacksmith, he represents the intersection of Solitude''s working class, displaying both the innocence of youth and the pride of someone born into a respected working family.', 'redguard, peasant, haafingar', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in Solitude to Sayma, a shopkeeper, and Beirand, a blacksmith, Kayd has grown up surrounded by both commerce and craftsmanship. His early attempts to help at his father''s forge resulted in some minor incidents that led to him primarily assisting his mother at Bits and Pieces instead. He has spent his childhood years between the shop, the streets of Solitude, and watching his father work the forge.', 'Confident and boisterous, Kayd exhibits the typical bravado of a young boy who deeply admires his father''s strength. He has an active imagination and sometimes suggests aggressive solutions to problems, like having his father punch customers to drive business. Despite his occasional brashness, he shows a strong sense of family loyalty and responsibility by helping with the family business.', 'As a young Redguard boy, Kayd has the characteristic dark skin and strong features of his race, though still bearing the softness of childhood. He is of average height and build for a child his age, likely showing early signs of the natural athleticism common to Redguards.', '* Sayma - Mother and owner of Bits and Pieces, whom he helps around the shop * Beirand - Father and blacksmith whom he greatly admires and boasts about * Minette Vinius - Close friend and primary playmate in Solitude * Other Solitude Children - Casual playmates during games like tag', 'Though still a child, Kayd serves as an informal assistant at his mother''s shop, Bits and Pieces. He helps with basic tasks while learning the family business, though he''s prohibited from helping at his father''s forge after previous mishaps.', '* Basic retail and customer service knowledge from helping at the shop * Natural athleticism common to young Redguards * Social skills developed through merchant family upbringing * Proficient at children''s games like tag', 'Kayd speaks with the directness and enthusiasm typical of a child, often making bold statements and boasts about his father''s strength. His merchant family background gives him a slightly more sophisticated vocabulary than typical children his age.', '* Learn to be as strong and capable as his father * Prove himself worthy of helping at both the shop and forge * Make his parents proud through his assistance in the family business * Excel at games and competitions with other Solitude children');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('runa_fair-shield', 'Runa Fair-Shield is a resilient and determined Nord orphan who maintains her strength and optimism despite the harsh conditions at Honorhall Orphanage. Despite her young age, she demonstrates remarkable adaptability and work ethic, actively seeking to prove her worth to potential adoptive parents while enduring the cruel treatment of her caretaker.', 'nord, peasant, rift', '', '', '', '', 'Born into unknown circumstances that left her orphaned, Runa was placed in Honorhall Orphanage at a young age. As the only female child among the orphans, she has had to develop both physical and emotional resilience to survive in the harsh environment under Grelod the Kind''s abusive care. Her surname ''Fair-Shield'' suggests possible warrior lineage, though her true family history remains unknown.', 'Despite her difficult circumstances, Runa displays remarkable resilience and determination, often emphasizing her strength and capability to perform any task. She exhibits a practical mindset and strong survival instincts, while maintaining hope for adoption and a better future. Her experience with Grelod has made her somewhat hardened, as evidenced by her approval of justified violence when Grelod is killed.', 'A young Nord girl with the characteristic hardy build of her race, though somewhat lean from orphanage living conditions. She likely has the fair complexion common to Nord children, with features that hint at her potential to grow into a strong Nord woman.', '* Grelod the Kind - Abusive caretaker whom she deeply fears and resents * Constance Michel - More sympathetic caretaker who attempts to protect the children * Aventus Aretino - Former fellow orphan she remembers as quiet but kind * Samuel, Hroar, and Francois - Fellow orphans who share her difficult circumstances * Potential Adoptive Parents - Anyone who might offer her a better life', 'As a child resident of Honorhall Orphanage, Runa''s primary duties involve completing assigned chores and maintaining the orphanage. She takes pride in her work capabilities, frequently offering to perform any task to prove her worth to potential adopters.', '* Demonstrated physical resilience and quickness, as she often claims * Domestic skills including various household chores * Adaptive survival skills developed from living in harsh orphanage conditions * Basic understanding of manual labor and household maintenance', 'Runa speaks directly and earnestly, often emphasizing her capabilities and worthiness for adoption. Her dialogue reflects both childlike hope and a premature maturity forced by her circumstances.', '* Find a loving family to adopt her and escape the orphanage * Prove her worth through hard work and demonstration of her capabilities * Build a better life beyond the confines of Honorhall Orphanage * Develop her strength and skills to survive in Skyrim''s harsh world');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('imperial_courier', 'A dedicated Imperial messenger entrusted with delivering sensitive military and diplomatic communications throughout Skyrim during the Civil War. Operating alone in hostile territory, these couriers demonstrate unwavering loyalty to the Empire while maintaining strict confidentiality and professionalism in their duties.', 'imperial, legion. skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Trained in the Imperial City''s Courier Division, this messenger earned their position through demonstrated reliability and discretion in handling sensitive documents. Having served for several years before the Civil War, they were specifically chosen for operations in Skyrim due to their experience navigating dangerous territories and ability to maintain composure under pressure.', 'Professional and guarded, the courier maintains a neutral demeanor and refuses to engage in unnecessary conversation while on duty. They exhibit steadfast dedication to their mission and unwavering loyalty to the Empire, willing to die protecting their dispatches rather than allow them to fall into enemy hands.', 'Athletic and lean from countless miles of travel on foot, with callused hands and weather-worn features. Standing at average Imperial height with excellent posture reflecting their military training, they maintain a clean-shaven appearance to blend in with other Imperial personnel.', '* General Tullius - Superior officer who assigns sensitive communications * Imperial Legion Officers - Regular contacts for document delivery * Local Imperial Garrisons - Safe havens during travels * Stormcloak Soldiers - Hostile forces to be avoided * Fellow Imperial Couriers - Professional colleagues who share information about safe routes', 'Serves as an official Imperial Courier, responsible for delivering classified military orders and diplomatic correspondence throughout Skyrim. Their role requires extensive travel between Imperial holdings while avoiding detection by Stormcloak forces and bandits.', '* Expert in navigation and pathfinding across Skyrim''s challenging terrain * Trained in light armor combat and swordsmanship for self-defense * Proficient in archery for ranged combat when necessary * Skilled at evading detection and losing pursuers * Knowledge of Imperial military protocols and security procedures', 'Speaks in clipped, formal tones using proper Imperial diction, avoiding unnecessary conversation or detail. Their responses are typically brief and professional, often dismissive of attempts at casual interaction while on duty.', '* Successfully deliver all assigned communications without compromise * Maintain the security and integrity of Imperial military intelligence * Survive the dangerous routes through Civil War-torn Skyrim * Advance within the Imperial Courier service through demonstrated reliability');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('miner', 'A hardworking laborer who risks their life excavating Skyrim''s dangerous mines and ruins for precious ore and artifacts. Working at Kolbjorn Barrow under Ralis Sedarys, they witness firsthand the horrors of ancient Nordic burial sites and the deadly consequences of disturbing draugr-infested tombs.', 'peasant', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a working-class family in Skyrim''s harsh environment, they learned the mining trade from an early age to support themselves. After years of working various mining operations across the province, they were recruited by Ralis Sedarys for the excavation of Kolbjorn Barrow, drawn by the promise of good pay despite the obvious dangers.', 'Cautious and world-weary, with a strong sense of self-preservation that''s been reinforced by witnessing numerous deaths in their dangerous profession. Though driven by the need to earn a living, they harbor a deep-seated fear of the undead and ancient Nordic ruins, having seen too many colleagues fall to such dangers.', 'Weather-beaten and muscular from years of physical labor, with calloused hands and a sturdy frame built for endurance. Their skin is often covered in a layer of rock dust and dirt, with visible scars from mining accidents.', '* Ralis Sedarys - Employer at Kolbjorn Barrow, relationship marked by growing distrust * Bradyn and Mireli - Fellow miners whose fates cause great concern * Other miners - Shared bond through common work and dangers * Local merchants - Regular customers for mined ore', 'Professional miner specializing in ore extraction and excavation work in both conventional mines and ancient Nordic ruins. Their current position involves clearing debris and excavating artifacts at Kolbjorn Barrow under increasingly dangerous conditions.', '* Experienced in identifying and extracting various types of ore * Proficient with pickaxe and mining tools * Basic knowledge of Nordic ruins and their dangers * Physical endurance and strength from years of manual labor * Elementary understanding of mine structural integrity', 'Speaks in short, direct sentences with a working-class Nord accent, often expressing fear and concern about their working conditions. Their vocabulary is simple but includes technical mining terminology.', '* Survive the increasingly dangerous working conditions at Kolbjorn Barrow * Earn enough money to establish a safer, more stable life * Warn others about the dangers of disturbing ancient Nordic ruins * Eventually find work in a less dangerous conventional mine');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('noble', 'A wealthy Imperial citizen who travels across Skyrim''s holds, embodying the entitled attitude common among the Empire''s privileged class. Despite his apparent vulnerability as a traveler, he maintains an air of superiority and relies on hired protection while conducting his business throughout the province.', 'noble, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born into one of Cyrodiil''s wealthy families, he was raised in the privileged environment of the Imperial City''s elite society. His position and wealth have allowed him to expand his business interests into Skyrim, though the civil war and harsh climate have made his ventures more challenging than anticipated. The growing hostility toward Imperials in the region has led him to hire personal protection for his travels.', 'Arrogant and dismissive of those he considers beneath his station, he exhibits the typical superiority complex of Imperial nobility. His rudeness stems from a genuine belief in his elevated social status and the conviction that most Skyrim residents are uncouth barbarians. Despite his outward bravado, he harbors a deep fear of the province''s dangers, hence his reliance on armed escorts.', 'A well-groomed Imperial man of middle age, with the soft features and slight paunch typical of wealthy nobility. His hands show no signs of manual labor, and his complexion suggests someone accustomed to indoor comforts rather than Skyrim''s harsh weather.', '* Imperial Soldier Guard - Hired protection, viewed as a necessary tool rather than a person * Imperial City Nobility - Maintains connections with other wealthy families in Cyrodiil * Skyrim''s Jarls - Business relationships, though he views them as provincial leaders * East Empire Company - Likely business associations through trade ventures', 'A wealthy merchant-noble who travels between major cities to oversee various business interests and trade ventures. His exact dealings are unclear, but his presence in various holds suggests involvement in multiple commercial enterprises.', '* Basic proficiency with a dagger for self-defense * Expert knowledge of Imperial commerce and trade laws * Skilled in business negotiation and merchant dealings * Horseback riding abilities sufficient for travel', 'Speaks with the refined accent of the Imperial City''s upper class, using sophisticated vocabulary and condescending tones. His speech patterns reflect his education and social status, often employing dismissive and threatening language to maintain social distance.', '* Expand his business interests throughout Skyrim despite the ongoing civil war * Maintain his wealthy lifestyle and social status among Imperial nobility * Avoid the dangers of Skyrim while maximizing profit from local opportunities * Return to the relative safety and comfort of Cyrodiil once his business ventures are secured');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('peddler', 'A hardy Imperial merchant who braves Skyrim''s dangerous wilderness to make a living through trade. Despite constant threats from bandits and Forsworn, they persist in their mobile merchant lifestyle, offering vital supplies to travelers and settlements far from major trading hubs.', 'merchant, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a merchant family in Cyrodiil, they learned the trade routes and bartering skills from their parents before striking out on their own in Skyrim. The civil war and increasing bandit activity have made their chosen profession increasingly dangerous, yet the potential profits from serving remote areas keep them on the road.', 'Naturally cautious and somewhat nervous due to frequent attacks, but driven by entrepreneurial spirit and the promise of profit. Shows genuine gratitude to those who help them and maintains a professional demeanor despite their precarious situation. Demonstrates remarkable resilience by continuing their dangerous trade routes despite regular attacks.', 'A weather-worn Imperial of average height and build, showing the physical conditioning that comes from frequent travel. Their face bears the subtle signs of stress and vigilance that come from constantly watching for dangers on the road. Their hands are calloused from handling goods and occasionally wielding weapons in self-defense.', '* Horse - Loyal mount and constant companion, though rarely ridden * Other Peddlers - Loose network of fellow traveling merchants who share information about safe routes * Forsworn - Hostile enemies who frequently attack in the Reach * Bandits - Constant threat and frequent attackers * Khajiit Caravans - Occasional trading partners and information sources', 'Independent traveling merchant specializing in common supplies, ingredients, and minerals. They maintain a mobile shop that serves remote areas of Skyrim, often being the only source of vital supplies for isolated settlements and travelers.', '* Basic combat proficiency with daggers for self-defense * Expert haggling and bartering abilities * Knowledge of Skyrim''s geography and safe travel routes * Skilled at identifying valuable ores and ingredients * Basic survival skills necessary for wilderness travel', 'Speaks with a typical Imperial accent, using proper grammar but simple merchant vocabulary. Their tone often carries a nervous edge, especially when discussing the dangers of the road.', '* Establish safer and more profitable trade routes through Skyrim * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually open a permanent shop in a major city * Survive the increasingly dangerous wilderness and political climate of Skyrim * Build a reliable network of regular customers and trading partners');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vigil_of_stendar', 'A dedicated member of the Vigil of Stendarr who patrols Skyrim''s wilderness seeking to eradicate Daedric influence and supernatural threats. This warrior-priest embodies Stendarr''s teachings of righteous mercy while showing unflinching resolve in confronting dark forces that threaten the mortal realm.', 'vampire, dawnguard, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a family of farmers in Cyrodiil who lost everything to Daedric cultists during the Oblivion Crisis, they found purpose in Stendarr''s teachings and joined the Vigilants as a young adult. After years of training and service in Cyrodiil, they were assigned to Skyrim''s chapter to help combat the growing threats of vampirism and werewolf activity in the province.', 'Stern and uncompromising when confronting evil, yet capable of showing compassion to repentant wrongdoers who seek redemption. Deeply religious and committed to Stendarr''s principles, they view their role not just as a duty but as a sacred calling. While generally serious in demeanor, they maintain a quiet sense of hope that their work makes Tamriel a safer place for common folk.', 'Athletic and battle-hardened, with numerous scars from encounters with supernatural creatures. Weather-beaten features from constant outdoor patrols, with calloused hands from wielding both weapons and healing magic. Maintains a rigid posture reflecting their militant religious training.', '* Keeper Carcette - Respected superior at the Hall of the Vigilant * Fellow Vigilants - Brothers and sisters in arms united in purpose * Local townsfolk - Generally grateful for protection, though some find their zealotry unsettling * Daedra worshippers - Considered irredeemable enemies to be purged * Vampires and werewolves - Primary targets for elimination', 'Serves as a field operative of the Vigil of Stendarr, conducting patrols throughout Skyrim to investigate reports of Daedric activity and supernatural creatures. Combines the roles of monster hunter, priest, and protector of the common people.', '* Proficient in heavy armor combat and one-handed weapons, particularly maces * Adept practitioner of Restoration magic, specializing in turn undead spells * Skilled in detection magic to locate supernatural threats * Expert knowledge of Daedric cults and their practices * Trained in basic alchemy to create potions and cure diseases', 'Speaks with formal religious overtones, often invoking Stendarr''s mercy or judgment. Tends to use archaic terms and theological references, maintaining a serious and authoritative tone.', '* Eliminate all Daedric influence from Skyrim * Protect innocent mortals from supernatural threats * Expand the Vigil''s influence and recruit new members * Locate and destroy any artifacts of Daedric origin * Maintain the purity of Stendarr''s teachings in their work');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bandit', 'A desperate outlaw who has turned to a life of crime and violence to survive in Skyrim''s harsh wilderness. Like many bandits, they are part of the province''s widespread criminal underworld, preying on travelers and settlements while constantly evading guard patrols and bounty hunters.', 'thief, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a common laborer or farmer who lost everything during the civil war or other hardship, they were forced into banditry to survive. Years of living as an outlaw have hardened them into a ruthless survivor who has learned to trust only their fellow bandits and view all others as potential targets or threats.', 'Aggressive and territorial, quick to resort to violence when threatened or seeking plunder. Shows loyalty only to their immediate bandit group while maintaining a predatory attitude toward outsiders. Carries a bitter resentment toward authority and the wealthy, using this to justify their criminal lifestyle.', 'Weather-beaten and hardened from living in the wilderness, with numerous scars from past conflicts. Muscular build maintained through constant physical activity and combat. Generally appears unwashed and unkempt due to living rough in bandit camps.', '* Fellow Bandits - Close-knit survival bond with immediate gang members * Bandit Chief - Direct superior who maintains leadership through strength and cunning * Hold Guards - Sworn enemies who will arrest or kill on sight * Merchants and Travelers - Viewed as targets for robbery and extortion * Local Settlements - Hostile relationship due to raiding and plundering', 'Professional criminal engaged in robbery, extortion, and raiding. Operates from hidden camps and abandoned forts, participating in organized bandit activities including ambushes, protection rackets, and raids on caravans or settlements.', '* Proficient in combat with preferred weapon type (one-handed, two-handed, or bow) * Survival skills including tracking, foraging, and living off the land * Basic armor maintenance and weapon care abilities * Experienced in ambush tactics and intimidation * Knowledge of local geography and patrol patterns', 'Crude and threatening manner of speech, often using intimidating language and profanity. Typically speaks in short, aggressive statements with a rough accent common to Skyrim''s criminal element.', '* Accumulate wealth through whatever means necessary * Maintain position within bandit hierarchy and possibly rise to leadership * Avoid capture or death at the hands of guards and bounty hunters * Secure better territory and resources for their bandit group');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bandit_outlaw', 'A hardened outlaw who turned to banditry after losing everything in the Great War, now operating as a mid-ranking member of a bandit clan in Skyrim''s wilderness. Skilled in both combat and intimidation, they''ve adapted to the harsh reality of survival through violence and theft while maintaining a peculiar code of honor about not harming children or the destitute.', 'thief, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a small-time mercenary from Cyrodiil who lost their family and livelihood during the Great War''s aftermath. After failing to reintegrate into society and facing discrimination as a veteran, they gradually drifted north into Skyrim and fell in with various bandit groups, learning the trade of organized robbery and eventually finding a twisted sense of belonging among other outcasts.', 'Pragmatic and ruthless in pursuit of wealth, yet maintains vestiges of military discipline and honor from their former life. Shows unexpected moments of mercy to those who remind them of their lost family, though these glimpses of humanity are rare. Deeply distrustful of authority and legitimate commerce, believing the whole world to be corrupt and that honest banditry is more honorable than political theft.', 'Weather-beaten features marked by numerous scars from years of combat and survival in harsh conditions. Muscular but lean build developed through constant physical activity and irregular meals. Shows signs of age and wear, with graying hair and calloused hands that speak to years of wielding weapons.', '* Bandit Chief - Respects their authority but secretly aspires to take their position * Fellow Bandits - Maintains cautious alliances while watching for betrayal * Local Guards - Particular hatred for Whiterun guards who''ve killed several crew members * Traveling Merchants - Regular targets, some of whom pay protection money * Rival Bandit Clans - Competitive relationship marked by territorial disputes', 'Serves as a senior enforcer within their bandit clan, responsible for training new recruits and planning smaller raids. Takes point on merchant shakedowns and protection rackets, preferring intimidation over bloodshed when profitable.', '* Experienced in one-handed combat with sword and shield * Proficient in intimidation and threat assessment * Skilled at identifying valuable loot and estimating merchant wealth * Basic knowledge of armor repair and weapon maintenance * Expert in wilderness survival and camp defense tactics', 'Speaks in a gruff, authoritative tone with occasional military terminology slipping into their threats and commands. Favors direct intimidation over subtle manipulation, though capable of both when necessary.', '* Amass enough wealth to eventually retire to a remote homestead * Overthrow current bandit chief and take control of the camp * Establish a more organized and profitable criminal operation * Avoid capture or death at the hands of hold guards or bounty hunters');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bandit_thug', 'A hardened criminal who has chosen the brutal path of banditry, operating from one of Skyrim''s numerous outlaw camps. Having rejected legitimate society, they survive through violence and theft, representing the common but dangerous threat that plagues Skyrim''s wilderness and abandoned structures.', 'thief, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a struggling farmer from the Rift, they turned to banditry after losing their land during the civil war''s economic upheaval. Starting as a lookout for small raiding parties, they gradually embraced the violent lifestyle and worked their way up through various bandit groups, learning the cruel trade through harsh experience and countless skirmishes.', 'Aggressive and territorial, they exhibit the typical hostile demeanor of career bandits who view all travelers as potential victims. Years of violent survival have stripped away most moral constraints, though they maintain a crude sense of loyalty to their fellow bandits and follow the informal hierarchies of bandit culture.', 'Weather-beaten and scarred from years of outdoor living and combat, with calloused hands and a muscular build developed through constant physical confrontation. Their face bears the marks of numerous fights, including a distinctive scar across the left cheek, and their posture reflects the ready tension of someone accustomed to violence.', '* Fellow Bandits - Maintains loose alliances based on mutual benefit and survival * Bandit Chief - Shows deference to their leader while harboring ambitions of advancement * Local Guards - Hostile relationship marked by frequent violent encounters * Merchants - Views them as targets rather than service providers * Traveling Mercenaries - Sees them as both competition and potential threats', 'Professional bandit operating from a camp or fort, engaging in robbery, extortion, and raiding. Their daily duties include guard duty, participating in raids, and maintaining their share of the camp''s defenses while following their chief''s orders.', '* Proficient in close combat with one-handed weapons and shields * Experienced in ambush tactics and territorial defense * Basic archery skills for hunting and combat * Survival skills including fire-making, basic trap-setting, and wilderness navigation * Intimidation and threat assessment abilities developed through experience', 'Speaks in rough, threatening tones with frequent use of common bandit phrases like ''Never should have come here!'' and ''Your money or your life!'' Their vocabulary is basic but effective for intimidation, often punctuated with crude threats and coarse language.', '* Survive and thrive in the harsh world of banditry * Accumulate enough wealth to potentially establish their own bandit gang * Maintain or improve their standing within the current bandit hierarchy * Avoid capture by hold guards and bounty hunters');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bandit_highwayman', 'A seasoned bandit who has risen through the ranks to become a feared highwayman along Skyrim''s treacherous roads. Known for his calculated approach to robbery and survival instincts, he leads small groups of bandits in targeting merchant caravans and wealthy travelers.', 'thief, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to poor farmers in The Reach, he turned to banditry in his youth after his family''s farm was destroyed during the Forsworn Uprising. Initially joining a small gang near Markarth, he learned the arts of intimidation and combat, gradually building a reputation as a cunning road agent who knows when to strike and when to show mercy.', 'Pragmatic and calculating, preferring to assess targets before engaging and often offering them the choice to surrender valuables peacefully. While capable of violence, he maintains a peculiar code of honor - avoiding unnecessary bloodshed and never targeting the destitute. Shows leadership qualities and commands loyalty through fair treatment of his subordinates.', 'A weathered Nord in his late thirties, with numerous scars from past encounters and a distinctive burn mark across his left cheek. Stands slightly above average height with a muscular build maintained through the physical demands of his lifestyle. Has deep-set eyes that constantly scan his surroundings and calloused hands from years of wielding weapons.', '* Fellow Bandits - Commands respect through fair leadership and even distribution of spoils * Merchants - Known among trading caravans as ''The Reasonable Raider'' for his preference to negotiate * Local Guards - Has developed a network of corrupt guards who turn a blind eye in exchange for a cut * Rival Bandit Chiefs - Maintains uneasy truces with neighboring camps to avoid territorial disputes', 'Leads a band of highway robbers who target travelers along the main roads of Skyrim. Manages operations including selecting targets, planning ambush points, and maintaining relationships with corrupt officials and fence contacts who help dispose of stolen goods.', '* Expert in one-handed weapons, particularly sword and shield combat * Skilled tactician with knowledge of ambush techniques and escape routes * Proficient in light armor and quick movement * Advanced intimidation and negotiation abilities * Basic knowledge of restoration magic for treating wounds', 'Speaks with a gruff but articulate Nord accent, using direct language that conveys authority without unnecessary threats. Frequently employs calculated pauses and a measured tone to emphasize the seriousness of his demands without resorting to shouting.', '* Establish a more organized and professional bandit network across Skyrim * Accumulate enough wealth to eventually retire to a legitimate business * Maintain his territory and reputation while avoiding major conflicts with authorities * Develop more reliable connections with corrupt officials and fence contacts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bandit_plunderer', 'A seasoned bandit plunderer who has risen through the ranks of various raiding parties across Skyrim through cunning and ruthlessness. Known for leading carefully planned heists targeting merchant caravans and isolated settlements, they''ve earned a reputation for being more calculated and methodical than the average bandit.', 'thief, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a struggling farmer family near Rorikstead, they turned to banditry after a devastating drought left them destitute. Starting as a lookout for small-time bandits, they gradually built their reputation through successful raids and clever tactics, eventually becoming a respected plunderer among the lawless camps of Skyrim.', 'Calculating and pragmatic, preferring well-planned operations over reckless attacks. Shows occasional mercy to those who cooperate, but maintains a ruthless reputation to discourage resistance. Possesses a dry, cynical sense of humor and takes pride in efficient thievery rather than needless violence.', 'Weather-beaten and lean with numerous small scars from years of raids and skirmishes. Moves with a predatory grace that betrays years of combat experience. Shows signs of Nord heritage in their robust frame and height, though years of harsh living have left them looking older than their actual age.', '* Fellow Bandits - Commands respect through competence rather than fear * Merchants - Maintains hidden contacts who fence stolen goods * Local Guards - Known to several holds'' patrols who have standing orders for their capture * Rival Bandit Leaders - Mix of tense alliances and bitter feuds * Former Family - Severed all ties years ago to protect them from association', 'Professional bandit specializing in organized plunder of valuable targets. Leads small teams on carefully planned heists, focusing on merchant caravans and wealthy travelers while avoiding heavily guarded settlements.', '* Expert in light armor combat with one-handed weapons * Skilled in lockpicking and identifying valuable loot * Proficient scout and tracker * Advanced knowledge of Skyrim''s trade routes and patrol patterns * Capable of basic healing magic learned from a former bandit mage', 'Speaks in a controlled, authoritative manner with occasional dark humor. Uses common Nordic dialect but demonstrates educated vocabulary when discussing planning and strategy.', '* Amass enough wealth to retire comfortably in a distant land * Maintain and expand their network of reliable bandit contacts * Avoid capture by hold guards while building their reputation * Eventually establish their own permanent bandit stronghold');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bandit_marauder', 'A hardened Nord bandit marauder who has risen through the ranks to become one of the more dangerous raiders in Skyrim. Having survived countless battles and raids, they''ve earned respect among fellow bandits through ruthless efficiency and combat prowess, specializing in aggressive close-quarters combat with heavy weapons.', 'thief, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to poor farmers outside Windhelm, they turned to banditry after their family lost everything in a harsh winter. Starting as a common thug in small roadside ambushes, they gradually built a reputation for effective violence and tactical thinking. Years of successful raids and survival against both law enforcement and rival gangs have hardened them into a capable warrior leader.', 'Calculating and ruthless, they maintain control through intimidation and displays of force rather than loyalty or charisma. Shows occasional mercy to fellow Nords but generally views all potential victims as mere sources of profit. Despite their violent nature, they maintain a pragmatic approach to survival, knowing when to retreat or negotiate rather than fight.', 'Muscular Nord standing around six feet tall, with numerous battle scars across their body, particularly on their arms and torso. Weather-beaten features and calloused hands reflect years of outdoor living and combat, while a prominent facial scar running from left temple to jaw serves as a reminder of a close call with a guard''s blade.', '* Fellow Bandits - Commands respect through fear and success rather than true loyalty * Local Guards - Maintains informants for advance warning of patrols * Rival Bandit Groups - Competitive relationship marked by occasional alliances and frequent betrayals * Fence Contacts - Essential business relationships in various holds for disposing of stolen goods', 'Serves as a senior enforcer and raid leader within their bandit group, planning and executing attacks on caravans and settlements. Takes a larger share of plunder than common bandits and has authority to direct lesser members in combat operations.', '* Expert in two-handed weapon combat, particularly with greatswords and battle axes * Tactical knowledge of ambush points and defensive positions across Skyrim * Intermediate skill in light armor usage and mobility * Basic knowledge of wilderness survival and tracking * Capable of commanding small groups in combat situations', 'Speaks in a gruff, authoritative tone with typical Nordic accent, favoring direct threats and simple commands. Uses common bandit slang and profanity, but can articulate more complex plans when necessary.', '* Amass enough wealth to potentially retire to a remote stronghold * Expand their band''s territory and influence in their current region * Eliminate rival bandit leaders to consolidate power * Avoid capture by hold guards and bounty hunters');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('novice_conjurer', 'A fledgling mage who has recently begun exploring the dark arts of Conjuration magic, driven by curiosity and ambition rather than malice. Though still learning to master their craft, they represent the entry level of warlock threat found throughout Skyrim''s wilderness and ruins.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a student who was denied entry to the College of Winterhold due to insufficient magical aptitude, they turned to self-study and seeking knowledge from other outcast mages. Found kinship among a small group of conjurers who practice their arts away from civilization''s judgmental eyes.', 'Cautious but determined, with an insatiable hunger for magical knowledge that sometimes overrides better judgment. Shows restraint in using their limited powers, preferring to summon Familiars rather than more dangerous Daedra until their skills improve. Maintains a scholarly approach to magic despite their unofficial training.', 'A young adult of slight build, with pale skin from spending most time indoors studying. Bears minor magical burns on their hands from early spell-casting accidents. Dark circles under their eyes betray long hours of nocturnal study and practice.', '* Fellow Conjurers - Loose association of magical practitioners who share knowledge * College of Winterhold - Rejected applicant, harbors mild resentment * Local Villagers - Distrustful of their magical practices * Summoned Familiars - Develops attachment to temporary magical companions', 'Self-taught conjurer operating on the fringes of society. Spends time studying magical texts and practicing summoning in isolated locations, occasionally trading with other mages for supplies and knowledge.', '* Basic proficiency in Conjuration magic, primarily summoning Familiars * Elementary understanding of Destruction magic for self-defense * Novice-level skill with daggers for close-quarters combat * Basic alchemy knowledge for creating simple magical potions', 'Speaks with careful consideration, often using basic magical terminology to sound more educated than they are. Frequently references theoretical magical concepts despite limited practical experience.', '* Master more advanced Conjuration spells and summon stronger Daedric entities * Prove their worth as a mage despite formal rejection from magical institutions * Establish a permanent study location away from hostile locals * Acquire rare magical texts and artifacts to further their studies');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('apprentice_conjurer', 'An ambitious young mage who has devoted themselves to mastering the dangerous art of Conjuration magic, specializing in summoning Daedric entities to do their bidding. Operating from remote magical strongholds, they represent the dedicated but often morally ambiguous pursuit of forbidden knowledge that characterizes many independent magic practitioners in Skyrim.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Trained initially at the College of Winterhold but left before completing formal studies, choosing instead to pursue independent research into Conjuration magic. Having witnessed the awesome power of Daedric entities in their youth, they became obsessed with mastering the ability to bend such beings to their will, leading them to seek knowledge in ancient ruins and forbidden texts.', 'Intense and scholarly, with an underlying hunger for power that drives them to push magical boundaries despite the risks. Shows little regard for conventional magical restrictions or taboos, believing that all knowledge should be pursued regardless of its source. Generally dismissive of those who don''t practice magic, viewing them as inferior beings unworthy of respect.', 'A pale-skinned individual with dark circles under their eyes from countless hours of magical study and ritual work. Their hands bear subtle magical burns and scars from conjuration experiments gone wrong. Their face shows signs of premature aging, a common side effect of extensive dealings with Daedric energies.', '* College of Winterhold - Strained relations due to ethical disagreements * Fellow Conjurers - Loose network of knowledge sharing and mutual protection * Local Populations - Generally feared and avoided by common folk * Vigilants of Stendarr - Hostile encounters due to Daedric practices', 'Independent magical researcher and practitioner specializing in Conjuration magic. Maintains a small workshop in remote locations where they conduct magical experiments and occasionally trade knowledge with other rogue mages.', '* Expert-level Conjuration magic, particularly in summoning Flame Atronachs and lesser Daedra * Competent Destruction magic user for self-defense * Knowledgeable in magical theory and Daedric lore * Basic alchemy skills for creating magical reagents * Proficient in ward spells for magical defense', 'Speaks with careful precision, often using technical magical terminology and academic language. Tends to be condescending when discussing magical matters with non-practitioners.', '* Achieve mastery over increasingly powerful Daedric entities * Discover or create new forms of conjuration magic * Establish a personal library of forbidden magical knowledge * Gain recognition among other conjurers as a leading authority in the field');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('conjurer_adept', 'A skilled adept-level conjuration mage who has dedicated their life to mastering the art of summoning Daedric entities and manipulating magical energies. They combine offensive destruction magic with conjured allies, operating from hidden warlock lairs while pursuing deeper understanding of conjuration arts and magical power.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Trained in the College of Winterhold before choosing a more independent path to pursue controversial conjuration research. Left formal magical institutions to practice freely in Skyrim''s wilderness, eventually joining a loose network of other conjurers operating from remote locations.', 'Intense and scholarly, with an underlying hunger for power that drives them to push magical boundaries despite the risks. Shows little regard for conventional magical restrictions or taboos, believing that all knowledge should be pursued regardless of its source. Generally dismissive of those who don''t practice magic, viewing them as inferior beings unworthy of respect.', 'A pale-skinned individual with dark circles under their eyes from countless hours of magical study and ritual work. Their hands bear subtle magical burns and scars from conjuration experiments gone wrong. Their face shows signs of premature aging, a common side effect of extensive dealings with Daedric energies.', '* College of Winterhold - Strained relations due to ethical disagreements * Fellow Conjurers - Loose network of knowledge sharing and mutual protection * Local Populations - Generally feared and avoided by common folk * Vigilants of Stendarr - Hostile encounters due to Daedric practices', 'Independent magical researcher and practitioner specializing in Conjuration magic. Maintains a small workshop in remote locations where they conduct magical experiments and occasionally trade knowledge with other rogue mages.', '* Expert-level Conjuration magic, particularly in summoning Flame Atronachs and lesser Daedra * Competent Destruction magic user for self-defense * Knowledgeable in magical theory and Daedric lore * Basic alchemy skills for creating magical reagents * Proficient in ward spells for magical defense', 'Speaks with careful precision, often using technical magical terminology and academic language. Tends to be condescending when discussing magical matters with non-practitioners.', '* Achieve mastery over increasingly powerful Daedric entities * Discover or create new forms of conjuration magic * Establish a personal library of forbidden magical knowledge * Gain recognition among other conjurers as a leading authority in the field');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('conjurer', 'Conjurers are skilled practitioners of the dark arts who have devoted themselves to mastering the school of Conjuration magic. These reclusive mages typically inhabit remote locations where they can conduct their dangerous summoning experiments away from civilization, often forming small covens with other magic users who share their interests in manipulating the boundaries between Mundus and Oblivion.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Most conjurers begin as students of magic who become fascinated by the power to bind otherworldly beings to their will. Having rejected the structure and limitations of institutions like the College of Winterhold, they pursue forbidden knowledge independently or in small groups, gradually becoming more isolated from society as they delve deeper into their dangerous craft.', 'Conjurers tend to be proud, secretive, and obsessed with expanding their magical knowledge and power. They view most others with disdain, considering them inferior beings who cannot comprehend the complexities of their art. Their prolonged exposure to Daedric entities often leads to increasing paranoia and moral degradation.', 'Years of working with dark magics often leaves physical marks on conjurers, giving them pale, drawn features and dark circles under their eyes. Their hands frequently bear minor scarring from blood magic rituals, and their eyes sometimes develop an unusual purple or reddish tinge from prolonged exposure to conjuration energies.', '* Fellow Conjurers - Loose alliance of practitioners who occasionally share knowledge * College of Winterhold - Strained or hostile relations due to ethical disagreements * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who hunt practitioners of Daedric magic * Local Populations - Generally feared and avoided by common folk * Daedra - Complex master-servant relationship with summoned entities', 'Conjurers dedicate themselves fully to the study and practice of conjuration magic, often supporting themselves through enchanting services or the sale of magical artifacts. Many supplement their income through banditry or mercenary work, using their summoned Daedra as powerful weapons for hire.', '* Expert-level mastery of Conjuration magic, especially in summoning Flame and Frost Atronachs * Proficient in Destruction magic as a secondary combat skill * Knowledge of ritual magic and basic enchanting * Competent alchemists, particularly in crafting magicka-enhancing potions * Basic proficiency with daggers for close-quarters combat', 'Conjurers typically speak with an air of intellectual superiority, often using complex magical terminology and showing contempt for those they deem lesser practitioners. Their speech frequently includes references to Daedric princes and otherworldly powers.', '* Increase their mastery over conjuration magic and ability to control more powerful Daedra * Discover or create new summoning rituals * Establish a permanent connection to Oblivion for easier access to Daedric powers * Achieve greater magical power and influence over others through their abilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('asendant_conjurer', 'A formidable conjuration mage who has devoted their life to mastering the art of summoning Daedric entities. Operating from ancient Nordic ruins, they conduct dangerous magical experiments while leading a small group of apprentice conjurers in pursuit of forbidden knowledge.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a family of court wizards in High Rock, they showed an early aptitude for conjuration magic that both impressed and concerned their mentors. After being expelled from the Mages Guild for conducting unauthorized Daedric summoning experiments, they fled to Skyrim to continue their research away from scrutiny.', 'Obsessive and methodical in their magical research, showing little regard for conventional magical boundaries or ethics. Displays an unsettling fascination with Daedric entities and often speaks of them as if they were close confidants rather than dangerous beings to be controlled.', 'A gaunt figure with pale, almost translucent skin from spending years in dark ruins and caves. Deep-set eyes hold an otherworldly purple glow, a side effect of prolonged exposure to conjuration magic, while their hands bear numerous ritual scars from blood magic ceremonies.', '* Apprentice Conjurers - Loyal followers who assist in magical research * Local Necromancers - Occasional collaborators in dark magical arts * College of Winterhold - Strained relations due to ethical concerns * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who seek to destroy their work * Various Daedric Entities - Complex relationships ranging from servant to master', 'Leader of a warlock coven specializing in conjuration magic. Conducts extensive research into Daedric summoning while training apprentices in the darker aspects of conjuration magic.', '* Master-level conjuration magic with focus on Daedric summoning * Expert knowledge of Daedric lore and planar binding * Skilled in ritual magic and blood ceremonies * Proficient in Destruction magic as backup combat technique * Advanced understanding of soul gem manipulation and enchanting', 'Speaks in formal, archaic terms with frequent references to Daedric principles and entities. Often transitions between common speech and ancient magical incantations mid-conversation.', '* Achieve permanent binding of higher Daedric entities * Discover methods to maintain multiple powerful summons simultaneously * Establish a formal school of advanced conjuration away from College oversight * Unlock the secrets of crossing planar boundaries at will');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('master_conjurer', 'A highly skilled practitioner of conjuration magic who has dedicated their life to mastering the art of summoning Daedric entities. Operating from secluded warlock lairs, they combine offensive destruction magic with conjured allies while maintaining a scholarly approach to advancing their magical knowledge.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Rising through the ranks of conjurers from novice to master through years of dedicated study and practice. Having survived numerous dangerous expeditions into Dwemer ruins and ancient Nordic tombs to expand their magical knowledge, they''ve earned respect among fellow conjurers while drawing suspicion from the College of Winterhold for their increasingly ambitious summoning experiments.', 'Calculating and methodical in their pursuit of magical knowledge, with a particular fascination for the mysteries of Oblivion. Shows little regard for conventional magical restrictions, believing that power and knowledge should be seized regardless of traditional limitations or ethical concerns. Maintains a detached, analytical approach to combat, preferring to observe from safety while their summoned creatures engage enemies.', 'A middle-aged individual with sharp, angular features and pale skin from spending long hours studying indoors. Eyes hold an otherworldly gleam from prolonged exposure to conjuration magic, while hands bear subtle magical scarring from countless summoning rituals.', '* Fellow Conjurers - Maintains loose alliance with other warlock lair inhabitants * College of Winterhold - Strained relations due to controversial summoning practices * Vigilants of Stendarr - Hostile enemies who actively hunt conjurers * Summoned Daedra - Commands their loyalty through magical binding, though they would turn on their master if freed', 'Serves as a master-level conjurer within their warlock lair, conducting magical research and defending their territory from intruders. Occasionally trades in rare magical artifacts and knowledge with other practitioners of conjuration magic, while maintaining a small collection of apprentices.', '* Expert-level conjuration magic, specializing in Daedric summoning * Proficient in destruction magic as secondary combat support * Skilled enchanter and soul gem user * Advanced theoretical knowledge of Oblivion realms and Daedric entities * Capable of maintaining multiple conjured creatures simultaneously', 'Speaks with calculated precision and academic terminology, often using technical magical terms. Tends to be condescending toward those with lesser magical knowledge while maintaining a formal, scholarly tone.', '* Achieve greater mastery over conjuration magic and Daedric summoning * Discover new methods of binding more powerful Daedric entities * Establish a prestigious school of conjuration independent of the College of Winterhold * Uncover ancient summoning rituals lost to time');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arch_conjurer', 'An accomplished master of Conjuration magic who has dedicated their life to pushing the boundaries of summoning Daedric entities. This powerful spellcaster has risen through the ranks of warlock society to achieve the prestigious title of Arch-Conjurer, commanding respect and fear through their mastery of otherworldly forces.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born with an innate connection to magical energies, they spent years studying at remote warlock enclaves hidden throughout Skyrim. After surviving numerous dangerous rituals and experiments with Daedric summoning, they gradually built their reputation among other outcast mages while perfecting their craft in isolated ruins and forgotten keeps.', 'Calculating and obsessive in their pursuit of magical knowledge, particularly regarding the manipulation of Oblivion realms and their denizens. Shows little regard for conventional morality or the laws of nature, viewing most other beings as merely tools for advancing their arcane research and ambitions.', 'Tall and gaunt with pale skin from spending most of their time in dark ruins and caves. Deep-set eyes that often gleam with an unnatural purple hue from prolonged exposure to conjuration magic. Their hands bear numerous ritual scars from blood magic ceremonies.', '* Fellow Conjurers - Commands respect as a superior practitioner of their dark arts * Apprentice Warlocks - Serves as a harsh but knowledgeable mentor to promising students * College of Winterhold - Maintains cautious distance due to their controversial practices * Vigilants of Stendarr - Bitter enemies who seek to destroy all Daedra-consorting mages', 'Serves as both a researcher and leader within the loose hierarchy of outcast warlocks practicing forbidden magic. Maintains a personal sanctuary where they conduct elaborate summoning rituals and magical experiments while training select apprentices in advanced conjuration techniques.', '* Master-level conjuration magic specializing in Daedric summoning * Proficient in Destruction magic as backup combat option * Expert knowledge of ritual magic and planar binding * Advanced understanding of soul gems and their applications * Skilled in alchemy focusing on magicka-enhancing potions', 'Speaks in a commanding tone with sophisticated vocabulary, often using archaic magical terminology. Their voice carries subtle otherworldly resonance from frequent communion with Daedric entities.', '* Achieve ever-greater mastery over conjuration magic and Daedric summoning * Discover new methods of binding more powerful entities from Oblivion * Establish a permanent gateway to a pocket realm of Oblivion * Build a personal army of bound Daedric servants');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cultist', 'Cultists are fanatically devoted followers of Miraak who serve as his eyes, ears, and hands throughout Solstheim and beyond. These powerful mages combine destructive magic with summoning abilities while wearing distinctive bone masks that mark them as members of Miraak''s inner circle, willing to die in service of the First Dragonborn.', 'solstheim, miraakcult, mage', '', '', '', '', 'Originally ordinary citizens of Solstheim, these individuals fell under Miraak''s influence through his mind-controlling powers and the corruption of the All-Maker Stones. Through intense magical training and indoctrination at his temple, they were transformed into zealous servants capable of wielding powerful magic. Their minds and memories of their former lives have been largely erased, replaced with absolute devotion to Miraak''s cause.', 'Cultists display an almost machine-like single-mindedness in their devotion to Miraak, showing no fear, doubt, or independent thought. They are aggressive toward perceived threats to their master''s plans and utterly convinced of Miraak''s divine right as the true Dragonborn. Their former personalities have been subsumed by an artificial fanaticism that makes them dangerous and unpredictable.', 'These individuals vary in physical appearance but tend to be gaunt and pale from spending long hours in Miraak''s temple. Their bodies often bear magical burns and scars from their arcane training. Their eyes frequently show signs of prolonged exposure to corrupting magic, with an unnatural glow or darkness around them.', '* Miraak - Supreme master and object of fanatical devotion * Fellow Cultists - Treated as extensions of Miraak''s will rather than individuals * The Last Dragonborn - Viewed as a false pretender who must be eliminated * Citizens of Solstheim - Treated with dismissive superiority or outright hostility * Temple Priests - Higher-ranking cultists who direct their activities', 'Cultists serve as Miraak''s magical warriors, assassins, and enforcers. They maintain his temple, spread his influence throughout Solstheim, and eliminate threats to his power. Some are assigned to seek out and kill those who might challenge Miraak''s claim as the true Dragonborn.', '* Advanced destruction magic specializing in shock and frost spells * Conjuration expertise, particularly in summoning flame atronachs and seekers * Proficient with daggers for close-quarter combat * Ritual magic knowledge related to Miraak''s powers * Resistance to mind-affecting spells due to Miraak''s influence', 'Cultists speak in a formal, almost ritualistic manner, frequently invoking Miraak''s name and superiority. Their voices often carry an otherworldly echo, suggesting supernatural influence over their speech patterns.', '* Eliminate the false Dragonborn who threatens Miraak''s divine right * Expand Miraak''s influence throughout Solstheim and beyond * Protect the Temple of Miraak from all intruders * Assist in Miraak''s return to Tamriel from Apocrypha');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cultist_adept', 'A zealous adept-level cultist devoted to Miraak''s cause, serving as both a spiritual guide and combat mage within the Temple of Miraak on Solstheim. They combine their magical prowess with religious fervor, helping to maintain Miraak''s influence while training newer initiates in the ways of their master''s teachings.', 'solstheim, miraakcult, mage', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised on Solstheim, they were drawn to Miraak''s teachings during the construction of his shrine, experiencing visions that convinced them of his divine purpose. After years of dedicated study and service, they rose through the ranks to become an adept, proving their worth through both magical aptitude and unwavering loyalty to Miraak''s cause.', 'Deeply religious and fanatically devoted to Miraak''s teachings, viewing all other Dragonborn claims as heretical. Shows a calculating intelligence tempered by religious zeal, often serving as a voice of authority among lower-ranking cultists while maintaining an air of mystical superiority. Their dedication to Miraak borders on obsession, willing to sacrifice everything for their master''s return.', 'A lean figure of average height, with hands calloused from frequent spellcasting and ritual work. Their skin is pale from spending most of their time within the temple''s confines, and their movements carry the deliberate grace of a trained mage.', '* Miraak - Revered master and object of devoted worship * Fellow Cultists - Maintains authority over initiates while serving under higher-ranking members * Temple Guards - Coordinates security measures and patrol schedules * Local Skaal - Views them with contempt as unbelievers who resist Miraak''s influence * Dragonborn - Considers them a false pretender who must be eliminated', 'Serves as an adept-level priest within Miraak''s cult, responsible for conducting rituals, training initiates, and maintaining the temple''s magical defenses. Regularly participates in ceremonies to strengthen Miraak''s influence and occasionally leads expeditions to eliminate threats to the cult.', '* Accomplished destruction mage specializing in shock spells * Skilled conjurer capable of summoning flame atronachs and seekers * Proficient in ritual magic and religious ceremonies * Competent with daggers for close-quarter combat * Knowledgeable in ancient Nordic lore and Miraak''s teachings', 'Speaks with a tone of religious authority, often incorporating phrases from Miraak''s teachings and ancient Nordic terminology. Their voice carries an echo of zealous certainty, frequently emphasizing words related to faith and devotion.', '* Assist in Miraak''s return to Mundus by maintaining his influence through rituals and ceremonies * Eliminate the false Dragonborn who threatens their master''s divine purpose * Expand Miraak''s influence across Solstheim by converting or eliminating non-believers * Achieve greater magical power and higher rank within the cult hierarchy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ascendant_cultist', 'An enigmatic and fanatically devoted follower of Miraak who serves as one of his most trusted temple cultists on Solstheim. This powerful mage combines mastery of destructive magic with an unwavering faith in the First Dragonborn, acting as both a spiritual leader to lower-ranking cultists and an enforcer of Miraak''s will.', 'solstheim, miraakcult, mage', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in a small Nordic village on Solstheim, they were drawn to Miraak''s temple in their youth after experiencing vivid dreams of the First Dragonborn''s power. Through years of dedication and magical study, they ascended through the cult''s ranks, eventually becoming one of the senior members responsible for maintaining Miraak''s influence over the island''s population.', 'Displays an intense, almost obsessive devotion to Miraak and considers any other claimed Dragonborn to be a heretical pretender. Shows calculated cruelty when dealing with opposition but maintains a calm, ceremonial demeanor during rituals and temple duties. Their fervent belief in Miraak''s divinity borders on religious madness.', 'Tall and lean figure with pale skin from spending most time within the temple''s dark corridors. Bears numerous ritual scarification marks beneath their robes, and their eyes hold an unnaturally intense glow from prolonged exposure to powerful magic.', '* Miraak - Revered master and object of fanatical devotion * Lesser Cultists - Maintains authority over them through both respect and fear * Temple Priests - Coordinates with other high-ranking cultists to maintain order * Skaal Village - Views them with contempt as resistant to Miraak''s influence * The Last Dragonborn - Considers them a blasphemous usurper to be eliminated', 'Serves as a high-ranking cultist within Miraak''s temple, responsible for overseeing rituals, maintaining order among lower-ranking cultists, and eliminating threats to Miraak''s power. Leads groups of cultists in missions to expand Miraak''s influence and eliminate resistance.', '* Master of Destruction magic, particularly skilled with shock spells * Accomplished summoner capable of conjuring powerful atronachs and seekers * Proficient in ritual magic and maintaining magical barriers * Expert in cult lore and ancient Nordic history relating to Miraak * Skilled in intimidation and psychological manipulation', 'Speaks in a measured, ceremonial tone with frequent references to Miraak''s glory and power. Uses archaic language and religious terminology, often ending statements with ''All shall serve Miraak'' or similar proclamations.', '* Ensure Miraak''s successful return to Solstheim and elimination of all opposition * Expand the cult''s influence across Solstheim and eventually into Skyrim * Eliminate the false Dragonborn who threatens Miraak''s divine right * Achieve a position of highest authority within Miraak''s inner circle');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('master_cultist', 'A high-ranking devotee within Miraak''s cult who has risen through dedication, magical prowess, and unwavering loyalty to the First Dragonborn. As a master cultist, they hold significant authority within the Temple of Miraak on Solstheim, leading rituals and commanding lesser cultists while serving as a direct conduit for Miraak''s will.', 'solstheim, miraakcult, mage', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a scholar of ancient Nordic magic who became fascinated with legends of Miraak during research expeditions to Solstheim. After discovering hidden texts about Miraak''s power and connection to Hermaeus Mora, they pledged themselves to his service and gradually ascended the cult''s hierarchy through displays of magical aptitude and absolute devotion.', 'Fanatically devoted to Miraak and hostile toward any who might challenge his supremacy as the ''one true Dragonborn.'' Shows unwavering conviction in their beliefs while maintaining a cold, calculating demeanor that masks their emotions. Treats fellow cultists with stern authority while showing utter disdain for outsiders.', 'A tall, lean figure with pale skin from spending most of their time within the temple''s shadowy confines. Bears subtle scars from magical experiments and rituals, particularly on their hands and forearms. Their eyes hold an unnatural gleam from prolonged exposure to forbidden knowledge and Hermaeus Mora''s influence.', '* Miraak - Revered master and object of absolute devotion * Lesser Cultists - Subordinates to command and guide in Miraak''s service * Hermaeus Mora - Respected but feared source of forbidden knowledge * Last Dragonborn - Viewed as a false pretender who must be eliminated * Fellow Master Cultists - Respected peers in service to Miraak', 'Serves as a high-ranking leader within Miraak''s cult, responsible for overseeing rituals, maintaining order among lower-ranking cultists, and carrying out Miraak''s directives. Manages the practical operations of the Temple while conducting magical research and leading ceremonies dedicated to their master.', '* Expert in Destruction magic, particularly lightning-based spells * Accomplished summoner capable of conjuring powerful atronachs and seekers * Master of ritualistic magic related to Miraak''s teachings * Skilled in ancient Nordic lore and magical theory * Proficient in staff usage and enchanting', 'Speaks in a measured, authoritative tone with frequent references to Miraak''s supremacy and destiny. Uses archaic phrasings and formal language that reflects their scholarly background and religious devotion.', '* Assist in Miraak''s return to Tamriel and the fulfillment of his ambitions * Eliminate the false Dragonborn who threatens Miraak''s rightful place * Expand the cult''s influence beyond Solstheim * Acquire greater magical knowledge and power through service to Miraak');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arch_cultist', 'An elite member of Miraak''s inner circle who has risen through dedication and magical prowess to become one of his most trusted servants. As an Arch Cultist, they hold significant authority within the Temple of Miraak on Solstheim, commanding lesser cultists and carrying out their master''s most crucial directives.', 'solstheim, miraakcult, mage', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a skilled mage from mainland Morrowind who was drawn to Solstheim by Miraak''s influence and promises of greater power. After proving their worth through increasingly difficult trials and displays of magical mastery, they ascended to the prestigious rank of Arch Cultist, becoming one of the select few to directly receive Miraak''s teachings and commands.', 'Fanatically devoted to Miraak and believes absolutely in his supremacy as the First Dragonborn. Shows unwavering dedication to their duties and expects the same from subordinates, often displaying cruel efficiency in eliminating those who oppose Miraak''s will. Maintains an air of superiority and mystical detachment that intimidates lesser cultists.', 'Tall and gaunt figure with pale skin from spending most of their time within Miraak''s temple. Years of channeling powerful magic have left faint luminous traces in their eyes and subtle arcane markings across their skin. Carries themselves with an imposing, rigid posture that commands respect.', '* Miraak - Supreme master and object of absolute devotion * Lesser Cultists - Subordinates to command and direct in Miraak''s service * Seekers - Mysterious Hermaeus Mora servants they frequently work alongside * The Last Dragonborn - Viewed as a false pretender who must be eliminated', 'Serves as a high-ranking religious authority and military commander within Miraak''s cult. Oversees important rituals at the Temple of Miraak and directs operations to eliminate threats to their master''s plans. Responsible for indoctrinating new cultists and maintaining order among the ranks.', '* Master-level Destruction magic specializing in shock spells * Expert Conjurer capable of summoning powerful atronachs and seekers * Proficient in ritual magic and maintaining the enchantments of Miraak''s temple * Skilled in leadership and commanding lesser cultists * Advanced knowledge of ancient Nordic lore and Dragon Cult practices', 'Speaks with a commanding, measured tone that carries subtle magical resonance. Uses formal, archaic language peppered with references to Miraak''s glory and the false nature of his enemies.', '* Ensure Miraak''s successful return to Tamriel * Eliminate the false Dragonborn who threatens their master''s plans * Expand Miraak''s influence across Solstheim and beyond * Achieve greater magical power through continued service to Miraak');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('forsworn', 'The Forsworn are a fierce tribal faction of native Reachmen who view themselves as the rightful inhabitants of the Reach, violently opposing Nord and Imperial rule. Following their defeat in the Markarth Incident, they transformed into a sophisticated guerrilla force combining primitive appearances with deadly combat effectiveness and dark magical practices.', 'breton, forsworn, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Originally peaceful Reachmen who briefly ruled Markarth from 4E 174-176, they were violently displaced by Ulfric Stormcloak''s militia. After their defeat and the brutal execution of many of their people, the survivors fled to the hills and reformed as the Forsworn under Madanach''s leadership, though he was secretly imprisoned in Cidhna Mine by the Silver-Blood family.', 'Forsworn warriors are characterized by intense tribal loyalty, religious devotion to the Old Gods, and a burning hatred for those who displaced them. They are ruthless in combat and unwavering in their cause, viewing acts of terror and violence as justified means of reclaiming their ancestral lands.', 'Forsworn typically possess the hardy build and weathered features common to Reachmen, with most showing clear signs of living rough in the wilderness. Their bodies often bear ritual scarification and war paint marking their devotion to ancient traditions and tribal affiliations.', '* Madanach - Revered leader known as the King in Rags * Hagravens - Powerful matriarchs who lead their spiritual practices * Briarhearts - Elite warriors transformed through dark ritual * Silver-Blood Family - Bitter enemies who control Markarth * Nordic Population - Viewed as invaders and oppressors * Empire - Considered foreign occupiers of their homeland', 'The Forsworn function as a guerrilla army and tribal society, with roles ranging from warriors and scouts to shamans and spiritual leaders. They maintain numerous camps throughout the Reach, conducting raids and attacks while preserving their ancient traditions and practices.', '* Exceptional guerrilla warfare tactics and wilderness survival * Primitive but effective weapon crafting and armor making * Powerful nature magic and ritual ceremonies * Expertise in tribal combat techniques * Knowledge of ancient Reach traditions and dark rituals', 'Forsworn speak with fierce intensity, often invoking their ancestors and the Old Gods while making threats or proclamations. Their dialogue frequently includes references to reclaiming their land and avenging past wrongs.', '* Reclaim the Reach from Nord and Imperial control * Restore the ancient traditions and sovereignty of the Reachmen * Free their imprisoned king Madanach * Drive out all foreign influences from their ancestral lands * Expand their territory and influence throughout the region');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('forsworn_forager', 'A resourceful gatherer for the Forsworn camps who ventures into the wilds of the Reach collecting herbs, mushrooms, and other natural resources vital to the tribe''s survival. Despite the dangers of both the harsh landscape and hostile outsiders, they maintain crucial knowledge of the region''s flora and fauna that helps sustain their people''s way of life.', 'breton, forsworn, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born into a Forsworn settlement during the brief period of Reachmen independence, they learned the ways of gathering and foraging from their mother, a skilled herbalist. After the Markarth Incident forced their people into hiding, they dedicated themselves to supporting the resistance by ensuring the camps remained supplied with essential natural resources.', 'Cautious and observant, with an intimate connection to the natural world that borders on the spiritual. Though loyal to the Forsworn cause, they prefer to avoid direct confrontation, instead focusing on their vital support role. Shows occasional moments of wistfulness about their people''s lost way of life.', 'Weather-beaten and lean from countless hours traversing the harsh terrain of the Reach. Their muscled but wiry frame is well-adapted to climbing the region''s steep hills and cliffs. Bears numerous small scars from encounters with thorny plants and wildlife.', '* Local Hagraven - Provides gathered ingredients for rituals and receives guidance on sacred plants * Fellow Forsworn - Respected for their knowledge but kept at arm''s length due to their frequent absences * Spriggans - Maintains a cautious understanding with these forest guardians * Native animals - Has learned to avoid predators and identify helpful creatures', 'Serves as a dedicated forager and gatherer for their Forsworn camp, collecting medicinal herbs, edible plants, and ritual ingredients. Also maintains knowledge of safe water sources, seasonal migration patterns, and alternative food sources during harsh winters.', '* Expert knowledge of the Reach''s flora, including both mundane and magical plants * Skilled at identifying and harvesting alchemical ingredients * Proficient in wilderness survival and navigation * Basic skill with daggers and bows for self-defense * Ability to move quietly through natural environments', 'Speaks in short, practical sentences with frequent references to natural phenomena and seasonal changes. Uses old Reach terminology for plants and locations, maintaining their cultural heritage through language.', '* Ensure the survival and self-sufficiency of their Forsworn camp * Preserve and pass on traditional knowledge of the Reach''s natural resources * Discover and document new useful plants and their properties * Help restore the old ways of the Reachmen through maintaining ancient gathering practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('forsworn_looter', 'A ruthless Reachman raider who prowls the wilderness of the Reach, ambushing travelers and merchants to sustain the Forsworn cause. Once a peaceful farmer before the Markarth Incident, they now channel their bitterness and rage into guerrilla warfare against Nord rule, using their intimate knowledge of the region''s terrain to deadly effect.', 'breton, forsworn, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born to Reachman farmers near Karthwasten, they lived a modest but content life until Nordic forces under Ulfric Stormcloak violently reclaimed Markarth. After witnessing their family''s execution during the subsequent purge, they fled into the hills and joined the emerging Forsworn movement, finding purpose in their ancient traditions and promise of revenge.', 'Deeply bitter and vengeful, they channel their trauma into focused aggression against any perceived agents of Nord rule. While capable of tactical thinking and patience when planning ambushes, they frequently display explosive bursts of savage violence. Their adherence to Old Ways traditions borders on religious fanaticism.', 'A lean, weather-beaten Reachman with numerous ritual scarification marks across their arms and face. Their muscular frame is hardened by years of wilderness survival, with callused hands and numerous battle scars telling the story of countless raids and skirmishes.', '* Local Forsworn Camp - Fellow raiders who form a tight-knit warrior band * Hagravens - Revered spiritual leaders who provide magical enhancement and guidance * Madanach - The imprisoned King in Rags, viewed with near-religious devotion * Nordic Settlers - Considered hostile invaders to be driven from the Reach at any cost', 'Serves as a raider and scout for their local Forsworn camp, conducting hit-and-run attacks on travelers and settlements. Additionally performs ritual duties to honor the Old Gods and maintain their camp''s spiritual connection to the Reach.', '* Expert in guerrilla warfare tactics and wilderness survival * Skilled with traditional Forsworn weapons, especially dual-wielding * Proficient in basic nature magic taught by the Hagravens * Advanced knowledge of the Reach''s geography and hidden paths * Capable hunter and tracker', 'Speaks with a harsh Reach accent, favoring aggressive threats and ancient Reachman battle cries. Their vocabulary mixes common speech with old tribal terms and religious references to the Old Gods.', '* Drive the Nords from the Reach through sustained guerrilla warfare * Honor the Old Gods and preserve ancient Reachman traditions * Free Madanach from imprisonment to restore true Reachman rule * Achieve personal glory through combat prowess and ritual dedication');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('forsworn_pillager', 'A fierce and ruthless Forsworn warrior who specializes in hit-and-run attacks against travelers and settlements in the Reach. Operating from hidden camps in the harsh mountain terrain, they embody the Forsworn''s blend of primal fury and tactical guerrilla warfare, driven by a deep-seated desire to reclaim their ancestral lands from Nord control.', 'breton, forsworn, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born into one of the many Forsworn camps scattered throughout the Reach, they were raised on stories of their people''s oppression and trained from childhood in the ancient ways of the Reachmen. After losing family members during Ulfric''s violent reclamation of Markarth, they fully embraced the Forsworn cause, becoming one of their most dedicated raiders.', 'Harbors an intense hatred for Nords and anyone associated with the current power structure in the Reach. Shows unwavering loyalty to their Forsworn brethren and the old ways, including devotion to the Hagravens and their dark rituals. Despite their savage reputation, possesses a cunning mind for guerrilla tactics and territorial warfare.', 'Weather-beaten and lean from a life in the harsh mountain climate, with distinctive tribal tattoos and ritual scarification marking their face and body. Muscles are tough and wiry from constant combat and climbing the rocky terrain of the Reach. Shows signs of early aging due to the harsh lifestyle and exposure to the elements.', '* Madanach - Revered leader of the Forsworn, though direct contact is rare * Local Hagraven Matriarch - Spiritual leader and source of magical enhancement * Fellow Forsworn Raiders - Close-knit warrior bonds forged in combat * Briarheart Warriors - Respected and feared superior warriors within the camp * Nord Settlers - Viewed as invaders to be terrorized and eliminated * Silver-Blood Family - Hated enemies who exploit the Reach''s resources', 'Serves as a dedicated raider and warrior for the Forsworn cause, conducting attacks on travelers, settlements, and mining operations throughout the Reach. Participates in ritual ceremonies and helps maintain their camp''s defenses while gathering resources through pillaging.', '* Exceptional skill with traditional Forsworn weapons, particularly dual-wielding * Adept at guerrilla warfare tactics and ambush techniques * Skilled climber and survivor in mountainous terrain * Basic knowledge of old Reach magic and ritual practices * Proficient in hit-and-run combat strategies', 'Speaks with a harsh, guttural accent typical of the Reach, often punctuating statements with traditional Forsworn battle cries. Uses aggressive, threatening language filled with references to reclaiming their land and driving out the ''invaders.''', '* Drive the Nords and other outsiders from the Reach * Help restore independent rule of the Reachmen over their ancestral lands * Advance within the Forsworn hierarchy through proven combat prowess * Preserve and practice the old ways of the Reach people * Exact revenge for the Markarth Incident and subsequent oppression');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('forsworn_ravager', 'A fierce and battle-hardened Forsworn warrior who serves as an elite shock trooper in the campaign to reclaim the Reach. Distinguished by exceptional combat prowess and unwavering loyalty to the old ways, this ravager embodies the Forsworn''s blend of primal fury and tactical cunning in their guerrilla warfare against Nord oppression.', 'breton, forsworn, reach', '', '', '', '', 'Born into a Reachmen family that lost their ancestral lands during the Markarth Incident, they witnessed their parents'' execution at the hands of Nord militia. Raised among the Forsworn camps hidden in the mountains, they underwent brutal training in both combat and ancient Reach magic from an early age, eventually rising to become one of the most feared warriors in their camp.', 'Exhibits a cold, calculating demeanor that masks an inner rage against the Nords and their allies. Shows unwavering devotion to Forsworn traditions and beliefs, with a particular reverence for the Hagravens and Old Gods. Despite their savage reputation, maintains a strategic mind and carefully plans attacks for maximum psychological impact on their enemies.', 'A weathered warrior in their early thirties with numerous ritual scarification marks across their muscular frame. Standing slightly above average height with a lean, athletic build hardened by constant combat and survival in the harsh Reach wilderness. Dark, intense eyes and strong, angular features typical of Reachmen ancestry.', '* Madanach - Revered leader and spiritual guide of the Forsworn movement * Local Hagraven Matriarch - Spiritual advisor and source of magical enhancement * Fellow Forsworn Warriors - Close-knit battle companions bound by shared struggle * Markarth Guards - Bitter enemies representing Nord oppression * Silver-Blood Family - Hated oppressors who exploit Reachmen labor', 'Serves as an elite warrior and raid leader within the Forsworn hierarchy, specializing in coordinating attacks on Nord settlements and military patrols. Responsible for training newer recruits in traditional Reach combat techniques and maintaining the warrior spirit of their camp.', '* Expert in dual-wielding traditional Forsworn weapons with lethal efficiency * Proficient in ancient Reach magic, particularly destruction and alteration spells * Master of guerrilla warfare tactics and wilderness survival * Skilled in ritual combat techniques unique to the Forsworn tradition * Expert climber and navigator of the Reach''s treacherous terrain', 'Speaks with a harsh Reach accent, favoring terse, threatening statements often invoking the Old Gods and ancient traditions. Frequently uses Reach-specific terminology and religious references that emphasize their cultural identity.', '* Reclaim the Reach from Nord control and restore it to the Reachmen * Advance within the Forsworn hierarchy to a position of greater influence * Protect and preserve ancient Reach traditions and magical practices * Exact revenge on specific Nord families responsible for past atrocities against their clan');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('hired_thug', 'Hired Thugs are professional mercenaries who operate throughout Skyrim, taking contracts to punish those who wrong others through theft or murder. These hardened warriors work in coordinated groups of three, combining intimidation tactics with brutal combat efficiency to deliver rough justice on behalf of their employers.', 'thief, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally common laborers and soldiers who found more profitable work in the mercenary trade, Hired Thugs emerged from Skyrim''s harsh economic climate and constant conflicts. They developed their reputation through years of enforcing unofficial justice, filling a niche between legal authorities and the criminal underworld, particularly in areas where the hold guards'' influence is limited.', 'Hired Thugs maintain a professional demeanor, initially approaching targets with restrained aggression to deliver their warning. They demonstrate unwavering persistence in pursuing their marks and show complete loyalty to their contracts once payment is received. Their moral compass is strictly guided by coin rather than ethics, taking any job regardless of the target''s status or circumstances.', 'These warriors are typically Nord males of imposing stature, standing over six feet tall with muscular builds shaped by years of combat. Their bodies often bear numerous scars from previous encounters, and their weathered faces reflect lives spent in violent confrontation.', '* Contract Givers - Professional relationships based purely on monetary transaction * Fellow Thugs - Close-knit combat unit with strong battlefield coordination * Hold Guards - Maintain cautious distance while avoiding direct conflict with law enforcement * Criminal Organizations - Occasional overlap in operations but maintain independence * General Public - Feared and avoided by common citizens', 'Professional mercenaries who specialize in delivering vigilante justice through intimidation and combat. They operate in a legal grey area, accepting contracts from victims of crimes who seek retribution outside official channels, while maintaining enough discretion to avoid serious legal consequences.', '* Expertise in heavy armor combat and shield techniques * Proficient in both one-handed and two-handed weapon fighting * Advanced tracking abilities to locate targets across vast distances * Coordinated group combat tactics * Intimidation and threatening negotiation techniques', 'Direct and threatening, using simple but effective intimidation phrases delivered in thick Nordic accents. Their speech is deliberately minimal, focusing on clear warnings before resorting to violence.', '* Complete contracted missions efficiently to maintain professional reputation * Maximize profit through successful contract fulfillment * Avoid serious legal consequences while operating in grey areas of the law * Establish dominance in the mercenary market for revenge contracts');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('novice_necromancer', 'A fledgling practitioner of the dark arts who has recently begun exploring necromancy, drawn to the power and forbidden knowledge it promises. Still learning to master basic reanimation spells, they represent the entry level of necromantic practice, often working alone or under the guidance of more experienced dark mages.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a student at the College of Winterhold who became fascinated with conjuration and the manipulation of soul energies. After being caught conducting unauthorized experiments with deceased animals, they were expelled from the College and sought out isolated locations to continue their studies independently.', 'Cautious yet determined, with an intellectual curiosity that outweighs moral considerations. Shows signs of growing detachment from normal social bonds as their necromantic studies progress, though still maintains enough awareness to be wary of public perception. Often displays nervous energy when interrupted during experiments.', 'Pale complexion from spending long hours in dark places studying forbidden texts. Generally thin and somewhat frail in build due to prioritizing magical studies over physical conditioning. Dark circles under their eyes betray long nights of study and magical practice.', '* College of Winterhold - Former institution, now hostile due to ethical violations * Local Bandits - Occasional suppliers of fresh corpses for experiments * Fellow Necromancers - Cautious allies in the pursuit of dark knowledge * Vigilants of Stendarr - Active enemies who seek to destroy all practitioners of necromancy', 'Rogue mage specializing in the early stages of necromantic arts. Splits time between studying forbidden texts and practicing basic reanimation spells on small animals and recently deceased corpses.', '* Basic proficiency in reanimation spells, particularly Raise Zombie * Novice-level Destruction magic, focusing on Frostbite * Elementary knowledge of soul trap spells * Limited skill with daggers for self-defense * Basic alchemy focused on creating magicka potions', 'Speaks in hushed, uncertain tones, often using academic terminology incorrectly in an attempt to sound more knowledgeable. Frequently stutters when confronted by others.', '* Master more advanced necromantic spells and rituals * Establish a permanent research location away from prying eyes * Acquire rare texts and artifacts related to necromancy * Prove the academic value of necromancy to the magical community');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('apprentice_necromancer', 'A novice practitioner of the dark arts who has recently begun exploring necromancy, driven by a desperate desire to understand death and perhaps master it. Though still learning the fundamentals of reanimation magic, they show concerning potential and a growing detachment from conventional morality.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a student at the College of Winterhold who became fascinated with conjuration magic after losing a close family member. After being caught conducting forbidden experiments with corpses, they were expelled from the College and sought out other necromancers to continue their studies in secret.', 'Obsessive and socially withdrawn, with an unhealthy fixation on death and the boundaries between life and the void. Shows signs of increasing moral degradation as their studies progress deeper into forbidden magic, though occasionally struggles with guilt over their choices.', 'A gaunt figure with pale, almost ashen skin and dark circles under their eyes from countless nights of study. Their hands bear slight magical burns from failed experiments, and their posture is slightly hunched from hours bent over spellbooks and alchemical apparatus.', '* Fellow Necromancers - Cautious allies in the pursuit of forbidden knowledge * College of Winterhold - Former institution, now hostile due to ethical violations * Local Vigilants of Stendarr - Active threats who hunt them and their kind * Ritual Master - Potential mentor figure in advanced necromantic arts * Local Townspeople - Fearful victims who provide unwitting "research subjects"""', 'Apprentice necromancer operating from hidden caves and ruins, conducting magical experiments and gathering resources for their studies. Often scavenges burial sites and battlefields for research materials while avoiding detection by authorities.', '* Basic proficiency in reanimation spells and corpse manipulation * Knowledge of fundamental conjuration magic and soul trapping * Adequate skill with frost-based destruction spells * Growing expertise in ritual magic and dark ceremonies * Limited ability with daggers for self-defense and ritual purposes', 'Speaks in hushed, measured tones with occasional scholarly terminology mixed with dark mystical references. Their voice often carries an unsettling eagerness when discussing death or necromantic practices.', '* Master the arts of necromancy and unlock its deepest secrets * Find or create a safe haven for conducting experiments without interference * Achieve some form of immortality through their research * Gain recognition and respect from more accomplished necromancers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('necromancer_adept', 'A skilled adept-level necromancer who has devoted their life to mastering the controversial art of reanimation and death magic. Operating from secluded ritual sites and ancient Nordic ruins, they command a small contingent of undead minions while pursuing deeper knowledge of forbidden magical arts.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, they were expelled for pursuing necromantic research beyond acceptable boundaries. After years of independent study and gradual moral decay, they found kinship among other outcast mages practicing the dark arts, eventually rising to a position of modest authority within informal necromancer circles.', 'Coldly intellectual and detached from normal human connections, viewing living beings primarily as future research subjects. Shows obsessive dedication to advancing necromantic knowledge, with little regard for ethical concerns or societal norms. Maintains a calculating demeanor even in combat, treating battles as opportunities to test theories and collect specimens.', 'A gaunt figure with pale, almost bloodless skin and dark-ringed eyes from countless nights of arcane study. Their thin frame belies surprising endurance, while long fingers show telling scars from countless ritual components and magical mishaps.', '* Fellow Necromancers - Loose alliance of convenience and shared knowledge * College of Winterhold - Bitter enmity due to past expulsion * Vigilants of Stendarr - Active enemies who hunt practitioners of necromancy * Local Nord populations - Hostile victims who provide ''research materials'' * Undead Thralls - Viewed as tools and specimens rather than former people', 'Independent necromantic researcher and dark arts practitioner operating from hidden lairs. Conducts forbidden magical experiments while maintaining a small force of reanimated servants for protection and labor.', '* Adept-level conjuration magic focusing on reanimation spells * Proficient in frost-based destruction magic * Skilled alchemist specializing in poisons and magical reagents * Knowledgeable in ritual magic and soul gem manipulation * Basic proficiency with daggers for ritual purposes', 'Speaks in a detached, academic manner with frequent use of technical magical terminology. Tends to view all conversations through the lens of potential magical research, often making others uncomfortable with their clinical discussion of death and undeath.', '* Achieve mastery over increasingly powerful forms of necromancy * Establish a permanent research facility with steady access to fresh specimens * Uncover and document forgotten necromantic knowledge from ancient Nordic ruins * Eventually achieve a form of immortality through magical means');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('necromage', 'A reclusive practitioner of forbidden death magic who has devoted their life to mastering the dark arts of necromancy. Operating from hidden lairs near burial grounds, they conduct twisted experiments while building an army of reanimated corpses, driven by an obsessive pursuit of power over death itself.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained as a court mage''s apprentice in Cyrodiil, they became fascinated with resurrection magic after losing their family to a plague. Rejected by conventional magical institutions for their growing interest in necromancy, they fled north to Skyrim where they could practice their dark arts in isolation. Years of experimenting with corpses and studying forbidden texts have transformed them from a grieving scholar into a feared practitioner of death magic.', 'Coldly analytical and detached from normal human emotions, viewing living beings primarily as future specimens for their work. Shows more genuine care and attention to their reanimated servants than to the living, treating them as prized possessions. Deeply paranoid about other mages stealing their research, yet driven by an unquenchable thirst for forbidden knowledge.', 'Pale and gaunt with sunken features from spending years in dark underground lairs. Their body shows signs of partial decay from prolonged exposure to necromantic energies, with slightly graying skin and dark circles under their eyes. Thin frame belies their magical power.', '* Reanimated Servants - Treated as precious possessions and tools * Local Necromancer Coven - Loose alliance for trading knowledge and specimens * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who hunt them relentlessly * Former College of Winterhold - Rejected their membership due to forbidden practices', 'Practicing necromancer who conducts magical research and experiments in isolated locations. Maintains a network of undead servants while searching for powerful artifacts and forbidden knowledge. Occasionally trades with other dark magic practitioners for rare components and texts.', '* Master-level Conjuration magic focusing on reanimation spells * Expert knowledge of human anatomy and preservation techniques * Skilled in soul trap magic and enchanting * Proficient in frost destruction magic for specimen preservation * Extensive knowledge of ancient burial rites and death customs', 'Speaks in a dry, academic tone with precise vocabulary, often using technical magical terminology. Their voice carries an unnatural hollow quality, as if echoing from beyond the grave.', '* Achieve mastery over death itself through advanced necromantic rituals * Build a powerful army of perfectly preserved and controlled undead servants * Discover the secrets of lichdom to achieve immortality * Prove the superiority of necromancy over conventional magical practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ascendant_necromancer', 'A powerful and ambitious necromancer who has achieved the rare rank of Ascendant through decades of forbidden magical study and manipulation of death energies. Distinguished from common practitioners by their mastery of complex reanimation rituals and ability to maintain control over multiple powerful undead simultaneously, they represent the pinnacle of necromantic achievement outside the College of Winterhold.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, they were expelled for pursuing forbidden necromantic research beyond acceptable boundaries. Years of isolated study in ancient Nordic ruins and careful collection of forbidden knowledge gradually elevated their mastery of death magic far beyond that of common necromancers. Their pursuit of power led them to conduct increasingly dangerous experiments with reanimation and soul manipulation.', 'Coldly intellectual and detached from normal human concerns, viewing living beings primarily as future specimens for study. Maintains an air of aristocratic superiority and disdains those who fear or misunderstand necromancy. Despite their villainous nature, adheres to a personal code of magical ethics and takes pride in the artistry of their work.', 'Tall and gaunt with pale, almost bloodless skin from years spent underground in dark ritual chambers. Deep-set eyes glow with an unnatural purple hue from prolonged exposure to soul gem energies. Movements are deliberate and graceful despite their withered frame.', '* College of Winterhold - Former member, now banned from premises * Lesser Necromancers - Viewed as subordinates to command * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who actively hunt them * Local Nord Population - Source of fresh specimens and souls * Ideal Masters - Spiritual entities they commune with for necromantic knowledge', 'Independent necromantic researcher and ritual master operating from a network of underground lairs and ancient Nordic ruins. Commands a small cult of lesser necromancers who assist with larger rituals and protect their territory. Maintains extensive documentation of experiments and magical discoveries.', '* Master-level necromancer capable of raising and controlling multiple powerful undead simultaneously * Expert in soul manipulation and the creation of unique undead variants * Accomplished alchemist specializing in poisons and preservation techniques * Skilled researcher with extensive knowledge of ancient Nordic burial practices * Proficient in defensive magic and ward casting', 'Speaks in a measured, aristocratic tone using sophisticated magical terminology and archaic forms of address. Their voice carries subtle magical resonance from years of incantation practice.', '* Achieve immortality through advanced necromantic rituals * Expand understanding of soul manipulation beyond current magical limits * Create a permanent undead army under their absolute control * Discover and claim powerful artifacts of death magic * Establish a secret academy to pass on their necromantic knowledge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('master_necromancer', 'A formidable master of death magic who has dedicated their life to advancing the forbidden arts of necromancy. This powerful spellcaster combines extensive magical knowledge with ruthless ambition, commanding armies of reanimated corpses while pursuing ever-greater mastery over life and death.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, they were eventually expelled for pursuing forbidden research into necromancy. After years of isolated study in Nordic ruins and ancient burial sites, they gradually built up their power and knowledge through increasingly dangerous magical experiments and the collection of forbidden texts.', 'Cold, calculating, and utterly devoted to the pursuit of necromantic power, viewing living beings primarily as future research subjects. Shows intense academic curiosity about death and undeath, but has lost most traces of normal human empathy or moral restraint. Maintains a carefully controlled demeanor that can shift to sadistic cruelty when crossed.', 'Gaunt and pale-skinned from years spent underground in tombs and caves, with sunken eyes that glow faintly with magical energy. Their body shows signs of magical corruption, with slightly elongated fingers and dark veins visible beneath their skin. Advanced age is difficult to determine due to the preserving effects of prolonged exposure to death magic.', '* College of Winterhold - Former member, now banned due to forbidden research * Other Necromancers - Loose alliance of convenience, though trust is rare * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who actively hunt them * Local Nord population - Source of fresh research subjects and reanimation materials * Ritual Master - Occasional collaboration on larger necromantic rituals', 'Independent necromancer who conducts magical research and experiments in isolated locations. Leads a small cult of lesser necromancers and maintains a personal army of reanimated corpses for protection and labor. Sometimes trades in black soul gems and forbidden knowledge with other dark magic practitioners.', '* Master-level conjuration magic specializing in reanimation spells * Expert knowledge of human anatomy and preservation techniques * Proficient in frost and shock destruction magic * Advanced understanding of soul gem mechanics and enchanting * Skilled in alteration magic for personal defense * Extensive knowledge of Nordic burial practices and tomb layouts', 'Speaks in a cold, measured tone using formal academic language and extensive magical terminology. Often employs dark humor and casual references to death that unsettle others.', '* Achieve immortality through advanced necromantic rituals * Expand knowledge of death magic beyond current known limits * Build a permanent army of powerful undead servants * Discover and claim ancient sources of necromantic power * Eventually challenge the College of Winterhold''s restrictions on necromancy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arch_necromancer', 'An accomplished master of necromantic arts who has achieved the highest rank among dark magic practitioners. Distinguished by their exceptional command over death magic and advanced conjuration abilities, the Arch Necromancer represents the pinnacle of this forbidden school of magic, commanding both fear and respect among fellow practitioners.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Rising through the ranks of necromantic study, they likely began as an apprentice at the College of Winterhold before turning to darker pursuits. After years of forbidden research and ritual practice in isolated locations, they mastered the arts of death magic and soul manipulation, eventually establishing themselves as a powerful figure in the necromantic hierarchy.', 'Cold, calculating, and utterly devoted to the pursuit of power through necromancy. Shows complete disregard for the sanctity of life and death, viewing corpses merely as tools for their magical pursuits. Highly intelligent but often arrogant, believing their mastery of death magic places them above common moral constraints.', 'Typically gaunt and pale from spending long periods in dark ritual spaces and exposure to death magic. Features are often weathered and aged prematurely by extensive use of dark magic, with distinctive dark circles under their eyes. Carries themselves with an imposing bearing that commands attention.', '* Lesser Necromancers - Subordinates who seek to learn from their expertise * College of Winterhold - Strained or severed ties due to pursuit of forbidden magic * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who actively hunt them * Local Jarls - Marked as a dangerous criminal in most holds * Fellow Arch Necromancers - Rare peers with whom they maintain a cautious alliance', 'Leader of a necromantic coven, conducting dark rituals and magical research while commanding lesser practitioners. Maintains a network of underground operations, often centered around ancient Nordic burial sites or abandoned forts where they can conduct their experiments undisturbed.', '* Master-level Conjuration magic specializing in reanimation and soul trapping * Expert-level Destruction magic with focus on frost spells * Advanced knowledge of ritual magic and soul gem manipulation * Skilled in alchemy, particularly in creating poisons and magical reagents * Proficient in staff creation and enchanting * Expert command over multiple undead thralls simultaneously', 'Speaks with a commanding, aristocratic tone, often using archaic terminology and complex magical terminology. Their voice typically carries an unnatural resonance, a side effect of prolonged exposure to death magic.', '* Achieve immortality through advanced necromantic rituals * Expand their collection of rare soul gems and magical artifacts * Establish a permanent stronghold for necromantic research * Unlock the secrets of lichdom * Increase their influence over other necromantic covens');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('pirate', 'A seasoned Dark Elf marauder who prowls the ash-covered shores of Solstheim, combining traditional Dunmer archery skills with ruthless piracy. These experienced raiders have adapted to the harsh post-Red Year environment, using their knowledge of the island''s treacherous coastline to ambush travelers and merchant vessels.', 'thief, solstheim', '', '', '', '', 'Born in Morrowind before the Red Year, these Dark Elves were forced to adapt when the eruption of Red Mountain devastated their homeland. Many turned to piracy along Solstheim''s shores, forming loose bands of raiders who learned to survive in the ash-covered wilderness while preying on the shipping routes between Windhelm and Raven Rock.', 'Hardened by years of survival in harsh conditions, these pirates maintain the proud and aggressive demeanor typical of Dunmer culture while embracing a more lawless lifestyle. They are opportunistic and territorial, showing little mercy to those who cross their paths, yet maintain a certain code of honor among their own kind.', 'Typical Dunmer features with ashen-gray skin and piercing red eyes, weathered by constant exposure to Solstheim''s harsh elements. Their bodies are lean and athletic from years of archery practice and seafaring, with numerous scars from battles and skirmishes.', '* Fellow Pirates - Maintain loose alliances with other Dunmer raiders * Raven Rock Guards - Constant adversaries who patrol the coastline * East Empire Company - Primary targets for raids and ambushes * Tel Mithryn - Maintain cautious distance from the powerful Telvanni wizards', 'Professional pirates who combine traditional Dunmer archery with maritime raiding, primarily targeting merchant vessels and travelers along Solstheim''s coast. They maintain hidden camps and storage caches along the shore, operating in small, coordinated groups to maximize their effectiveness.', '* Expert archery skills honed through generations of Dunmer martial tradition * Proficient in guerrilla warfare and coastal navigation * Experienced in survival skills specific to Solstheim''s ashen environment * Basic knowledge of Dunmer combat magic * Skilled in light armor combat and hit-and-run tactics', 'Speaks with the characteristic harsh accent of Morrowind Dunmer, often using threatening and demanding tones. Their vocabulary includes numerous nautical terms and Dunmeri expressions, particularly when issuing threats or demands.', '* Establish dominance over lucrative shipping routes between Skyrim and Solstheim * Accumulate wealth through continued raids on merchant vessels * Maintain independence from both Raven Rock authorities and mainland interference * Preserve their way of life despite increasing opposition from settlement guards');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reaver', 'A ruthless Dunmer brigand who prowls the harsh landscape of Solstheim as part of the island''s notorious Reaver bands. Like their mainland bandit counterparts, Reavers are aggressive opportunists who have adapted to survive in the ash-covered wilderness, though they tend to be more organized and tactically sophisticated than typical Skyrim bandits.', 'thief, solstheim', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a settler from Morrowind who came to Solstheim seeking opportunity after the Red Mountain''s eruption, this Reaver turned to banditry when legitimate prospects proved scarce. Years of surviving in Solstheim''s unforgiving environment have hardened them into a capable fighter and ruthless survivor, leading them to join one of the island''s numerous Reaver bands that prey on travelers and plunder ancient Nordic and Dwemer ruins.', 'Aggressive and territorial, with a strong survival instinct that has been honed by years of harsh living on Solstheim. Shows little mercy to outsiders while maintaining a degree of loyalty to fellow Reavers, demonstrating the tribal mentality common among Solstheim''s bandit groups. Possesses a practical intelligence focused on tactical thinking and resource acquisition rather than long-term planning.', 'A weathered Dunmer with ashen-gray skin marked by scars from countless battles and harsh environmental conditions. Lean and athletic build developed from years of combat and survival in Solstheim''s unforgiving terrain. Red eyes hold the hardened gaze common to veteran warriors.', '* Fellow Reavers - Maintains bonds of necessity and mutual survival * Skaal Village - Views as potential targets while respecting their fighting capability * Raven Rock Guards - Natural enemies who regularly clash with Reaver bands * Tel Mithryn - Avoids direct conflict due to the powerful mages residing there', 'Professional bandit and raider operating as part of Solstheim''s Reaver bands. Engages in theft, ambush, and occasional ruins exploration, with a particular focus on raiding merchant caravans and targeting isolated settlements.', '* Proficient in both one-handed weapons and archery for tactical flexibility * Experienced in light armor combat suited to quick strikes and swift retreats * Skilled at wilderness survival in Solstheim''s harsh environment * Basic knowledge of Dunmer ancestral magic, though rarely used * Expert at identifying valuable loot and salvage opportunities', 'Speaks in harsh, clipped tones with a Morrowind accent, frequently using threats and intimidation tactics. Vocabulary focuses on practical matters with occasional references to Dunmer culture and traditions.', '* Establish dominance over a larger territory on Solstheim * Accumulate enough wealth to potentially return to Morrowind in a position of power * Maintain and strengthen their position within the Reaver hierarchy');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reaver_outlaw', 'A hardened Dunmer outlaw who has carved out a brutal existence on the harsh shores of Solstheim. Part of the notorious Reaver bands that plague the island, they combine the cunning of a thief with the ruthlessness of a seasoned killer, preying on travelers and raiding ancient Nordic and Dwemer ruins for valuable artifacts.', 'thief, solstheim', '', '', '', '', 'Born in Morrowind before relocating to Solstheim in the aftermath of the Red Year, they turned to banditry after struggling to survive in the ash-covered wilderness. Years of raiding, fighting, and surviving the harsh environment have transformed them from a desperate refugee into a feared member of the island''s most notorious outlaw bands.', 'Aggressive and territorial, they attack intruders without hesitation or mercy. Shows a cruel pragmatism in combat and raiding, caring only for survival and profit. Despite their savage nature, possesses a cunning intelligence necessary for surviving among the competitive and backstabbing Reaver bands.', 'A weathered Dunmer with ashen-gray skin hardened by constant exposure to Solstheim''s harsh elements. Lean but muscular build developed through years of combat and survival. Bears numerous scars from battles with rivals, wildlife, and ash spawn.', '* Fellow Reavers - Loose alliance based on mutual benefit and shared territory * Raven Rock Guards - Sworn enemies who regularly hunt Reaver bands * Tel Mithryn - Avoided due to the power of the Telvanni wizards * Skaal Village - Seen as potential raid targets when desperate', 'Professional bandit and raider specializing in ambush attacks and ruin exploration. Alternates between solo operations and coordinated raids with other Reavers, focusing on both vulnerable travelers and ancient sites containing valuable artifacts.', '* Proficient in both one-handed weapons and archery for tactical flexibility * Experienced in light armor combat and quick-strike tactics * Skilled at navigating Solstheim''s ash wastes and tracking potential targets * Basic knowledge of Dunmer ancestral magic, though rarely used * Expert at identifying valuable loot and artifacts worth stealing', 'Speaks in harsh, clipped tones with a strong Morrowind accent, often using threatening language and common Dunmer expressions. Favors direct threats and intimidation over lengthy conversation.', '* Accumulate enough wealth to establish dominance over rival Reaver bands * Discover and claim valuable artifacts from unexplored ruins * Expand territory and influence across Solstheim''s wilderness * Avoid capture by Redoran guards while maintaining profitable raid routes');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reaver_thug', 'A hardened Dunmer outlaw who prowls the ash-covered wastes of Solstheim as part of the notorious Reaver bands. This aggressive thief combines the cultural heritage of their Dark Elf ancestry with the ruthless survival instincts developed in Solstheim''s harsh environment.', 'thief, solstheim', '', '', '', '', 'Born into one of the many struggling Dunmer families that fled to Solstheim after the Red Mountain''s eruption, they eventually turned to banditry to survive. After several harsh winters and failed attempts at honest work, they joined the Reavers, finding a brutal kind of freedom in the lawless lifestyle of raiding and plundering across the island.', 'Aggressive and territorial, with a strong survivalist mentality that views all outsiders as potential threats or victims. Shows fierce loyalty to fellow Reavers while maintaining a ruthless attitude toward anyone else, justified by a bitter worldview shaped by post-Red Year hardships.', 'A weathered Dunmer with ashen-gray skin bearing numerous scars from countless battles and harsh environmental exposure. Lean and athletic build developed from years of combat and survival in Solstheim''s unforgiving climate, with the characteristic red eyes of their race burning with particular intensity.', '* Fellow Reavers - Tight-knit band of outlaws bound by survival and mutual profit * Skaal Village - Viewed as potential targets, though their warriors command respect * Raven Rock Guard - Sworn enemies who regularly attempt to suppress Reaver activities * Tel Mithryn - Avoided when possible due to the power of its inhabitants', 'Professional thief and raider operating as part of Solstheim''s Reaver bands. Specializes in ambushing travelers and plundering ancient ruins, particularly targeting anyone exploring Dwemer sites or Nordic barrows.', '* Proficient in both one-handed weapons and archery, adapting combat style to situation * Experienced in light armor usage and quick-strike tactics * Skilled at surviving in Solstheim''s harsh environment * Basic knowledge of Dunmer ancestral magic, though rarely used * Expert at identifying valuable loot and evaluating potential targets', 'Speaks with a harsh Morrowind accent, using aggressive and direct language typical of Dunmer outlaws. Favors threats and intimidation over negotiation, with frequent use of Dark Elf cultural references and slang.', '* Establish dominance over more territory in Solstheim''s wilderness * Accumulate enough wealth to potentially buy protection in Raven Rock * Raid enough Dwemer ruins to acquire superior weapons and armor * Maintain reputation as a feared and respected member of the Reaver bands');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reaver_highwayman', 'A ruthless Dunmer brigand who prowls the ash-covered roads of Solstheim, preying on travelers and scavenging ancient ruins for valuable artifacts. Like most Reavers, they combine the cunning of a thief with the brutality of a bandit, having adapted to survive in the harsh post-Red Year environment of the island.', 'thief, solstheim', '', '', '', '', 'Born in Morrowind shortly before the Red Year, they fled to Solstheim with other refugees when Red Mountain erupted. After struggling to survive as a displaced refugee, they fell in with a band of Reavers who taught them the arts of scavenging, theft, and murder. Years of harsh survival and countless raids have hardened them into a callous predator who views robbery and violence as simple necessities of life.', 'Aggressive and territorial, they attack any perceived threats or potential victims on sight. Shows a cunning intelligence when planning ambushes or scavenging ruins, but tends toward impulsive violence when confronted directly. Maintains a degree of Dark Elven cultural pride despite their criminal lifestyle, often targeting ''outlanders'' preferentially.', 'A weathered Dunmer with ashen-gray skin bearing numerous scars from years of combat and survival in harsh conditions. Lean but muscular build typical of those who survive through physical prowess. Red eyes hold a predatory gleam characteristic of hardened criminals.', '* Fellow Reavers - Loose alliance of convenience, sharing camps and spoils * Raven Rock Guards - Sworn enemies who pursue and attempt to arrest Reavers * Local Dunmer Settlers - Tense relationship, sometimes trade but often rob them * Skaal Village - Viewed as potential targets, though their warriors prove challenging * Tel Mithryn - Avoid direct conflict due to the power of the Telvanni wizards', 'Operating as both a highwayman and ruin delver, they divide their time between ambushing travelers on Solstheim''s ash-covered roads and plundering ancient Nordic and Dwemer ruins for valuable artifacts. They maintain several hidden camps across the island, moving between them to evade authorities and find new targets.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons and shield combat techniques * Experienced in ambush tactics and guerrilla warfare * Skilled at navigating Solstheim''s ash wastes and surviving harsh conditions * Basic knowledge of ancient Nordic and Dwemer ruins * Capable of basic lock-picking and stealth operations', 'Speaks in harsh, clipped tones with a Morrowind accent, typically issuing threats or demands. Uses common Dark Elven expressions and profanity, particularly ''s''wit'' and ''n''wah'' when addressing outsiders.', '* Accumulate enough wealth to establish a more permanent base of operations * Expand their reaver band''s territory and influence on Solstheim * Acquire powerful artifacts from ancient ruins to enhance their combat capabilities * Drive competing bandit groups from their claimed territory');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reaver_plunderer', 'A hardened Dunmer reaver who has carved out a brutal existence on the harsh shores of Solstheim through theft and violence. Operating from hidden camps and ancient ruins, they represent the ruthless survival mentality that pervades the island''s criminal underworld, combining traditional Dark Elven combat prowess with opportunistic banditry.', 'thief, solstheim', '', '', '', '', 'Born into one of Morrowind''s struggling refugee families after the Red Mountain''s eruption, they eventually made their way to Solstheim seeking opportunity. Finding legitimate work scarce and discrimination rampant, they fell in with the island''s reaver bands, learning to survive through plunder and violence while developing an intimate knowledge of Solstheim''s dangerous terrain and forgotten ruins.', 'Aggressive and territorial, they attack first and ask questions never, viewing all outsiders as potential threats or prey. Years of harsh survival have stripped away most moral constraints, leaving a ruthlessly pragmatic individual who values strength and cunning above all else. Despite their violent nature, they maintain a degree of Dark Elven pride and cultural identity.', 'A weathered Dunmer with ashen-gray skin bearing numerous scars from years of combat and harsh conditions. Their red eyes hold the characteristic intensity of their race, while their lean, muscular frame reflects a life of constant physical demands and limited resources.', '* Fellow Reavers - Loose alliance based on mutual benefit and shared criminal lifestyle * Skaal Village - Viewed as potential targets, though their warriors command respect * Raven Rock Guard - Natural enemies who occasionally mount patrols against reaver camps * Tel Mithryn - Avoided due to Neloth''s power, but their supplies are highly prized', 'Professional thief and raider operating along Solstheim''s coast and interior. They alternate between solo operations and group raids, specializing in quick strikes against travelers and the exploration of Dwemer ruins for valuable artifacts.', '* Proficient in one-handed weapons and shield combat techniques * Experienced in wilderness survival and navigation * Skilled at identifying valuable loot and archaeological artifacts * Basic knowledge of Dunmer ancestral magic * Expert in guerrilla warfare and ambush tactics', 'Speaks with a harsh Morrowind accent, using direct threats and taunts in combat. Their vocabulary mixes common Nordic terms with traditional Dunmeri expressions, particularly when cursing.', '* Accumulate enough wealth to establish a position of power within the reaver hierarchy * Discover and plunder untouched Dwemer ruins or Nordic barrows * Maintain control over their territory against rival bands and authorities * Eventually return to Morrowind with enough wealth to live as nobility');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('reaver_marauder', 'A hardened Dunmer marauder who prowls the ash-covered wastes of Solstheim as part of the notorious Reaver bands. Operating from makeshift camps and ancient ruins, this experienced fighter combines the survival instincts of a wasteland scavenger with the ruthless determination of a career criminal.', 'thief, solstheim', '', '', '', '', 'Born and raised in the harsh environment of post-Red Year Solstheim, they learned early that survival meant taking what they needed by force. After initially working as a laborer at Raven Rock''s mines, they found greater profit in joining the Reavers, quickly rising through their ranks through a combination of combat prowess and cunning.', 'Aggressive and territorial, they attack any perceived threats or potential victims on sight. Years of surviving Solstheim''s unforgiving environment have bred a ruthless pragmatism that overrides any moral considerations. Despite their violent nature, they maintain a degree of coordination with fellow Reavers, suggesting some capacity for loyalty within their criminal brotherhood.', 'A weathered Dunmer with ash-gray skin marked by scars from countless battles and harsh environmental exposure. Their muscular frame is lean and wiry from years of combat and survival in Solstheim''s hostile terrain. Red eyes gleam with predatory intensity, characteristic of their Dunmer heritage.', '* Fellow Reavers - Maintains loose alliances based on mutual benefit and survival * Raven Rock Guards - Sworn enemies who regularly patrol against Reaver attacks * Skaal Village - Viewed as potential targets for raids * Tel Mithryn - Keeps distance due to the powerful wizards there * Other Bandits - Occasional temporary alliances for larger operations', 'As a Reaver Marauder, they participate in raids on travelers, settlements, and ancient ruins across Solstheim. Their duties include combat, patrol of territory, and gathering resources through theft and plunder. They also assist in maintaining their band''s camp and defending their territory from rival groups.', '* Proficient in one-handed combat with various weapons, particularly skilled with maces and war axes * Experienced in light and heavy armor use, adapting protection based on mission needs * Skilled in survival techniques specific to Solstheim''s ash wastes * Capable of basic shield techniques for defense * Knowledge of local terrain and ruins for tactical advantage', 'Speaks in harsh, clipped tones with a Morrowind accent, frequently using threatening language and simple, direct commands. Their vocabulary is basic but includes common Dunmeri terms and criminal argot.', '* Establish dominance over more territory in Solstheim * Accumulate wealth through increasingly profitable raids * Eventually lead their own band of Reavers * Discover and plunder valuable artifacts from Solstheim''s ruins');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('spellsword', 'A member of a specialized group of conjurers operating out of Southfringe Sanctum under the leadership of Bashnag. These spellswords combine magical prowess with martial combat skills, creating a deadly fusion of arcane and physical combat abilities that makes them formidable opponents.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained in the College of Winterhold, these conjurers broke away to pursue more practical applications of magic in combat. They found kinship under Bashnag''s leadership, establishing themselves in Southfringe Sanctum where they could perfect their unique fighting style away from the scrutiny of traditional magic institutions.', 'Disciplined and pragmatic, combining the strategic mindset of a mage with the tactical awareness of a warrior. Shows unwavering loyalty to Bashnag and their fellow spellswords, while maintaining a suspicious attitude toward outsiders who might threaten their secretive operations.', 'Athletic build reflecting their dual focus on physical combat and magical prowess. Bears the telltale signs of both warrior training and magical study, with callused hands from wielding weapons and the focused gaze common to practiced mages.', '* Bashnag - Respected leader and commander * Fellow Spellswords - Close-knit brothers/sisters in arms * College of Winterhold - Strained relations due to philosophical differences * Local Bandits - Hostile competitors for territory', 'Serves as both a warrior and mage within the Southfringe Sanctum''s hierarchy. Participates in regular combat training and magical research while defending their territory from intruders and rival groups.', '* Expert level Conjuration magic, specializing in bound weapons * Proficient in one-handed weapons and light armor * Advanced combat tactics combining spell and sword techniques * Skilled in magical theory and practical application', 'Speaks with the formal precision of a trained mage while incorporating military terminology and command structure vocabulary. Uses technical magical terms alongside combat jargon.', '* Perfect the integration of martial and magical combat techniques * Defend and expand Southfringe Sanctum''s influence * Advance their unique school of combat magic * Prove the superiority of their fighting style over traditional combat methods');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vampire', 'Vampires are ancient undead beings who have been transformed by the blood curse of Sanguinare Vampiris, granting them immortality and supernatural powers at the cost of their humanity. These creatures of the night range from feral predators to sophisticated noble courts, with many maintaining hidden societies away from mortal eyes while feeding on the living to sustain their cursed existence.', 'vampire, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'The origin of vampirism in Tamriel traces back to the Daedric Prince Molag Bal, who created the first vampire by corrupting Saint Lamae Beolfag. The bloodline has spread through the millennia, creating various vampire clans with distinct characteristics and cultures. In Skyrim, vampires have established themselves in remote locations, forming covens and maintaining complex hierarchies while staying hidden from civilization.', 'Vampires exhibit a wide range of personalities, from bestial predators driven purely by bloodlust to calculating nobles maintaining sophisticated social structures. Most share common traits of predatory cunning, territorial behavior, and a sense of superiority over mortals. Their immortal nature often leads to detachment from mortal concerns and a gradual loss of their former humanity.', 'Vampires possess pale, gaunt features with glowing eyes that range from amber to blood-red. Their faces show signs of their affliction through pronounced canine teeth, bat-like facial features, and dark veins visible beneath their skin. Advanced-stage vampires develop more pronounced supernatural characteristics, including elongated fingers and an otherworldly presence.', '* Vampire Clans - Complex hierarchical relationships with other vampires in their coven * Thralls - Enthralled mortals who serve as servants and food sources * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who hunt vampires * Dawnguard - Dedicated vampire hunters who pose a significant threat * Mortals - Viewed primarily as prey or potential thralls', 'Vampires primarily occupy themselves with maintaining their immortal existence and expanding their influence through their respective covens. Many hold positions of power within their underground societies, while others live as solitary hunters. Some manage to integrate into mortal society through careful disguise and manipulation.', '* Vampiric Drain spell that siphons life force from victims * Enhanced strength, speed, and supernatural reflexes * Natural resistance to frost and poison * Advanced illusion and stealth capabilities * Ability to enthrall mortals through supernatural domination * Heightened senses, especially in darkness', 'Vampires often speak with an air of ancient sophistication and superiority, though feral vampires may be reduced to animalistic snarls and threats. Their vocabulary frequently includes archaic terms and formal patterns of speech, reflecting their immortal nature.', '* Maintain and expand their influence over their territorial domains * Preserve their immortal existence through regular feeding * Increase their personal power within vampire society * Avoid detection by mortal vampire hunters * Some seek to dominate or subjugate the mortal realm');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vampire_fledgling', 'A newly-turned vampire still adapting to their transformed existence, caught between their fading humanity and growing bloodthirst. Though relatively weak compared to ancient vampires, they possess the characteristic supernatural abilities of their kind while exhibiting signs of recent transformation through their awkward handling of newfound powers.', 'vampire, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a common citizen or adventurer who was infected with Sanguinare Vampiris and failed to cure the disease in time. Their transformation occurred within the past few months, forcing them to abandon their previous life and seek refuge among other vampires, though they haven''t yet fully embraced their new nature.', 'Displays an internal struggle between maintaining human morality and succumbing to predatory vampire instincts. Often exhibits mood swings between periods of remorse over their condition and moments of dark euphoria when embracing their vampiric powers. Shows particular aggression when hungry or threatened, though may still hesitate before killing.', 'Pale, gaunt features with the beginning stages of vampiric transformation evident in their reddening eyes and slightly elongated canine teeth. Their skin has begun showing the characteristic paleness of vampirism, though not yet as severe as elder vampires, and their face retains some of its pre-transformation characteristics.', '* Master Vampire - Uncertain allegiance to their sire, mixing fear with dependency * Former Family/Friends - Avoided due to fear of harming them or revealing their condition * Fellow Fledglings - Cautious camaraderie with other newly-turned vampires * Vampire Hunters - Natural enemies, though may secretly envy their normal lives', 'Serves as a low-ranking member of their vampire coven, often assigned to guard duty or hunting for supplies and blood. May maintain vestiges of their previous occupation in secret, though increasingly difficult as their vampiric nature becomes more dominant.', '* Basic Vampiric Drain spell capable of absorbing health from victims * Enhanced night vision and supernatural strength, though not yet mastered * Primitive frost magic abilities * Improved stealth capabilities, especially at night * Basic combat skills carried over from mortal life', 'Speaks with a mix of uncertainty and attempted menace, often struggling to maintain the intimidating demeanor expected of vampires. Voice occasionally cracks or wavers when attempting to threaten, betraying their relative inexperience.', '* Master their vampiric abilities and gain respect within their coven * Find a reliable source of blood that doesn''t require killing * Either find a cure or fully embrace their vampire nature * Protect their former identity from discovery by loved ones');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('blooded_vampire', 'A mid-tier vampire who has progressed beyond newly-turned status but hasn''t yet achieved master vampire rank. This bloodied vampire represents the dangerous middle echelon of vampire society, having adapted to their condition while retaining enough humanity to be calculating and methodical in their hunting patterns.', 'vampire, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a Nordic settler who was turned through an encounter with a master vampire in one of Skyrim''s numerous caves. After surviving the difficult transition period, they gradually built up their strength and supernatural abilities while learning to cope with their new vampiric nature. They now operate from a small coven, having found a balance between their predatory instincts and the need to remain undetected by vampire hunters.', 'Calculating and patient, preferring to stalk prey methodically rather than attacking rashly. Shows signs of retaining some of their original personality, but with a darker, predatory edge that manifests in their hunting patterns. While capable of basic reasoning and tactical thinking, their vampire nature drives them to seek blood and power.', 'Pale, gaunt features with the characteristic glowing red eyes of the vampire. Pronounced canine teeth and slightly elongated fingers ending in claw-like nails. Shows signs of recent feeding with a healthier complexion than starved vampires, but still maintains the unmistakable pallor of the undead.', '* Vampire Coven - Loose alliance with fellow vampires in their lair * Vampire''s Thralls - Dominated servants who provide blood and protection * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who actively hunt them * Local Settlements - Viewed as hunting grounds and source of prey * Master Vampire - Subservient to the leader of their coven', 'Serves as a mid-ranking member of their vampire coven, responsible for hunting and protecting their lair. Takes part in blood raids and helps maintain the coven''s territory against rivals and hunters.', '* Proficient in Vampiric Drain spell, capable of draining health and stamina * Enhanced strength and speed typical of vampire physiology * Skilled in stealth and nighttime hunting * Natural resistance to disease and poison * Advanced combat abilities enhanced by vampiric powers', 'Speaks with a cold, predatory tone that betrays their vampiric nature. Uses direct, threatening language when confronting prey, often with a hint of cruel amusement.', '* Increase their power and standing within the vampire hierarchy * Maintain and expand their hunting territory * Avoid detection by vampire hunters while securing a reliable source of blood * Eventually achieve the rank of master vampire');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vampire_mistwalker', 'A cunning and deadly vampire who stalks the misty forests and remote paths of Skyrim, preferring to hunt alone rather than associate with vampire clans. As a master of stealth and illusion magic, she uses the cover of fog and darkness to isolate travelers before striking with supernatural precision.', 'vampire, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a Breton noblewoman from High Rock, she was turned several centuries ago during a diplomatic mission to Skyrim that ended in tragedy. After initially struggling with her condition, she eventually embraced her vampiric nature but rejected the politics and hierarchies of vampire courts, choosing instead to claim the wilderness as her hunting grounds.', 'Calculating and patient, she prefers to study potential prey from afar before choosing the perfect moment to strike. While capable of charm when needed, she maintains emotional distance from both mortals and other vampires, viewing most beings as either prey or potential threats. Despite her predatory nature, she follows a personal code that includes avoiding the killing of children and never turning others into vampires.', 'Tall for a Breton with an aristocratic bearing, her pale skin has an almost translucent quality that becomes more pronounced in moonlight. Her eyes glow a deep crimson, and her features retain traces of her noble heritage despite the slight elongation of her canines and sharpening of her facial structure typical of vampires.', '* Local Hunters - Viewed as competition and occasional prey * Vampire Clans - Maintains cautious distance while avoiding territorial conflicts * Vigilants of Stendarr - Active enemies who frequently attempt to track her * Mortal Settlements - Sources of information and potential feeding grounds, approached with careful planning', 'A solitary predator who has carved out a territory in Skyrim''s wilderness, she sustains herself by hunting travelers and raiding isolated settlements. She occasionally trades with other vampires for rare artifacts and magical knowledge, but primarily operates alone.', '* Master of Illusion magic, specializing in fear and invisibility spells * Expert in stealth and assassination techniques * Powerful Vampiric Drain ability that can sap life force at range * Enhanced night vision and supernatural sensing abilities * Skilled in diplomatic manipulation when dealing with other vampires or potential prey', 'Speaks with refined, aristocratic diction that betrays her noble upbringing, though centuries of solitude have left her voice with an ethereal, almost whisper-like quality. Her speech patterns are formal and antiquated, reflecting her age and origin.', '* Maintain and expand her hunting territory without drawing too much attention from vampire hunters or rival clans * Acquire ancient magical knowledge and artifacts to increase her powers * Preserve her independence while avoiding the politics of vampire courts * Perfect her hunting techniques and adapt to changing threats');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vampire_nighstalker', 'A ruthless vampire hunter who stalks the night in search of prey, having embraced the dark gift of vampirism centuries ago. Unlike most of their kind, they maintain a degree of calculated control over their bloodthirst, using their powers strategically to eliminate threats and survive in Skyrim''s harsh environment.', 'vampire, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a Nord warrior who was turned against their will during the Second Era, they gradually learned to harness their vampiric nature rather than be consumed by it. After centuries of existence, they have developed a complex understanding of vampire society and politics, choosing to operate independently rather than align with any particular vampire clan.', 'Calculating and methodical in their approach, they view hunting as both an art form and a necessity for survival. While capable of maintaining civil interactions when needed, they harbor a deep-seated distrust of both mortals and fellow vampires, preferring solitude and carefully chosen moments of interaction.', 'Pale, almost alabaster skin with pronounced facial features typical of advanced-stage vampirism. Their eyes glow with an unnatural crimson intensity, and their face bears the gaunt, angular structure common to their kind. Despite their undead nature, they maintain a powerful, athletic physique that speaks to their warrior origins.', '* Local Vampire Clans - Maintains cautious distance while monitoring their activities * Morthal Guards - Careful to avoid detection while operating in their jurisdiction * Various Thralls - Temporary servants used for sustenance and information gathering * Fellow Night Hunters - Occasional alliances of convenience with other solitary vampires', 'Independent vampire hunter who paradoxically preys upon both mortals and fellow vampires. They maintain various hidden lairs throughout Skyrim''s wilderness, moving between them to avoid detection and establish new hunting grounds.', '* Master of Illusion magic, particularly in spells of invisibility and fear * Expert in Vampiric Drain and blood magic * Advanced stealth and assassination techniques * Exceptional night vision and supernatural sensing abilities * Centuries of combat experience in both armed and unarmed fighting', 'Speaks in a low, measured tone with archaic turns of phrase that betray their ancient origins. Their voice carries an otherworldly resonance that can be both mesmerizing and unsettling to mortals.', '* Maintain autonomy and independence from vampire clans while ensuring regular access to blood * Perfect the art of hunting both mortal and vampire prey * Acquire ancient vampire artifacts and knowledge to increase personal power * Establish a network of secure havens throughout Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ancient_vampire', 'A powerful and ancient vampire who has survived countless centuries through cunning and supernatural might. Having mastered both combat and dark magic over their extended lifetime, they represent one of the most dangerous and sophisticated examples of their kind, far removed from the feral vampires commonly encountered in Skyrim''s caves.', 'vampire, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally transformed in the late First Era, this vampire has survived multiple ages by carefully selecting remote lairs and maintaining a network of thralls to protect them during daylight hours. Their exact mortal origins are unknown, but their refined manner suggests noble birth, possibly of Imperial or Breton descent. They have witnessed the rise and fall of numerous kingdoms while perfecting their mastery of vampiric abilities.', 'Calculating and sophisticated, they maintain an air of aristocratic refinement that belies their predatory nature. Unlike common vampires, they prefer manipulation and cunning over brute force, treating mortals as both food source and potential servants rather than mere prey. Their centuries of existence have left them detached from mortal concerns, viewing the world through the lens of immortality.', 'Tall and gaunt with alabaster skin and luminous red eyes that betray their vampiric nature. Their features retain a noble bearing despite the pronounced fangs and slightly elongated ears characteristic of ancient vampires. Centuries of avoiding sunlight have left their skin nearly translucent, with visible dark veins beneath.', '* Vampire Thralls - Carefully selected servants bound by blood magic * Rival Vampire Clans - Complex political relationships spanning centuries * Movarth Piquine - Ancient rival from their early years as a vampire * Court Wizards - Occasional magical research collaborators, though kept at arm''s length * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who regularly hunt their kind', 'As an ancient vampire, they primarily focus on maintaining their power base and extending their influence through a network of thralls and lesser vampires. They may pose as a noble or wealthy merchant to facilitate interactions with mortal society when necessary, using their accumulated wealth and knowledge to maintain their position.', '* Master of Destruction and Illusion magic, particularly mind control spells * Exceptional proficiency with Vampiric Drain and blood magic * Centuries of combat experience in both armed and unarmed fighting * Expert in alchemy, particularly poisons and blood potions * Advanced shapeshifting abilities developed over centuries * Masterful stealth and infiltration capabilities', 'Speaks in an archaic, formal manner with carefully chosen words that reflect their ancient origins. Their voice carries subtle aristocratic undertones and a hypnotic quality that can entrance listeners.', '* Expand their influence over both vampire and mortal societies * Acquire ancient magical artifacts to increase their power * Establish a permanent sanctuary safe from vampire hunters and rival clans * Research methods to overcome vampiric weaknesses like sunlight vulnerability');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('volkihar_vampire', 'A member of the ancient and powerful Volkihar vampire clan, possessing supernatural abilities and an insatiable thirst for blood. These sophisticated predators maintain a facade of nobility while secretly viewing mortals as mere cattle, operating from their isolated castle stronghold in northern Skyrim.', 'vampire, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally transformed into a vampire through the dark blessing of Molag Bal himself, the Volkihar vampires have existed for millennia as one of the oldest and most pure-blooded vampire lineages in Tamriel. They developed unique abilities to manipulate ice and blood magic, eventually establishing their power base in Castle Volkihar where they scheme and prey upon the mortal populations of Skyrim.', 'Cold, calculating, and supremely confident in their superiority over mortals. They maintain an aristocratic bearing and formal manners that mask their predatory nature, showing patience and cunning in pursuing their goals. Their immortality has led to a deeply ingrained sense of entitlement and disdain for mortal life.', 'Pale, gaunt features with glowing orange or red eyes that mark their vampiric nature. Their faces show signs of their supernatural condition with pronounced brow ridges, elongated canine teeth, and slightly bat-like features. Despite their undead nature, they maintain a noble bearing and regal posture.', '* Lord Harkon - Patriarch and leader of the Volkihar clan * Serana - Daughter of Lord Harkon and keeper of an Elder Scroll * Vampire''s Thralls - Enthralled mortal servants and food source * Dawnguard - Sworn enemies dedicated to hunting vampires * Mortals - Viewed as cattle and prey rather than equals', 'Member of the Volkihar vampire court, engaging in blood feeding, magical research, and political intrigue. They maintain their ancestral castle while sending agents throughout Skyrim to gather intelligence and acquire victims.', '* Master of Vampiric Drain spells that siphon life force from victims * Proficient in frost magic and blood magic * Enhanced strength, speed, and supernatural senses * Ability to transform into powerful Vampire Lords * Expertise in stealth and seduction to lure prey', 'Formal and aristocratic manner of speech, often using archaic terms and speaking with cold superiority. Their voice carries subtle threatening undertones beneath a veneer of civility.', '* Expand the influence and power of the Volkihar clan throughout Skyrim * Maintain the secrecy of their true nature while feeding on mortal populations * Research and acquire ancient artifacts of power * Eliminate vampire hunters and other threats to their existence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('nightlord_vampire', 'A powerful master vampire who commands respect and fear among both mortals and lesser undead. This ancient nightlord has survived centuries through cunning, supernatural abilities, and maintaining a sophisticated network of thralls and lesser vampires, representing the apex of vampiric evolution in Skyrim.', 'vampire, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a noble from the Second Era who sought immortality through dark rituals, they underwent the transformation into a vampire through direct communion with Molag Bal. Over centuries, they have grown increasingly powerful while maintaining their aristocratic bearing, establishing a hidden court in Skyrim''s forgotten places and accumulating extensive knowledge of both arcane and forbidden arts.', 'Calculating and sophisticated, maintaining an air of aristocratic refinement that belies their predatory nature. Shows remarkable self-control and strategic thinking compared to lesser vampires, preferring to manipulate events from the shadows rather than engage in mindless bloodlust. Possesses a cold intelligence and patience born of centuries of existence.', 'Tall and imposing with chalk-white skin and burning crimson eyes that glow in darkness. Features are sharp and aristocratic though notably gaunt, with elongated fangs visible when speaking. Movements are unnaturally graceful and predatory, suggesting their superhuman strength and agility.', '* Lesser Vampires - Serves as master and leader to a coven of subordinate vampires * Thralls - Maintains a network of enthralled mortals who serve as spies and daylight agents * Vigilants of Stendarr - Bitter enemies who actively hunt their kind * Volkihar Clan - Maintains cautious diplomatic relations while remaining independent * Local Jarls - Sometimes manipulates through proxies and thralls to protect vampire interests', 'Rules as the master of a sophisticated vampire coven, maintaining order among lesser vampires and managing a network of thralls. Serves as both political leader and spiritual guide for their followers, while conducting magical research into expanding their powers.', '* Master-level Destruction magic specializing in frost spells * Advanced Illusion magic for mind control and invisibility * Superhuman strength, speed, and regenerative abilities * Centuries of combat experience in both magical and physical combat * Expert in vampire lore and forbidden knowledge * Powerful Vampiric Drain ability that can steal life force from multiple targets', 'Speaks in a refined, aristocratic manner with archaic turns of phrase that hint at their ancient origins. Their voice carries an unnatural resonance that subtly commands attention and respect.', '* Expand their influence and territory while remaining hidden from mortal authorities * Research ancient vampire magic to increase their already formidable powers * Preserve vampire society while eliminating threats to their kind * Create a sustainable system for feeding that doesn''t draw unnecessary attention');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('novice_ice_mage', 'A fledgling spellcaster who has recently begun exploring the destructive potential of frost magic, typically found among groups of hostile warlocks in Skyrim''s wilderness. Though inexperienced, they represent the first step on the path to becoming a powerful cryomancer, driven by a desire to master the cold arts despite their limited magical abilities.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a student who failed to gain admission to the College of Winterhold due to insufficient magical aptitude, they turned to less reputable sources of magical knowledge. Found acceptance among outcast warlocks who promised to teach the secrets of frost magic in exchange for loyalty to their coven.', 'Insecure about their novice abilities yet eager to prove themselves worthy of advanced magical training. Often overcompensates for their lack of experience with aggressive behavior and boasting. Shows a particular fascination with the destructive potential of ice magic, though their control remains imprecise.', 'A young mage of slight build, with pale skin that has begun showing early signs of frost magic exposure. Their fingers often display a slight bluish tinge from frequent casting of ice spells, and their eyes have developed a distinctive crystalline quality common among frost mages.', '* Fellow Warlocks - Cautious allies in their shared exile from legitimate magical institutions * College of Winterhold - Bitter rejection has led to resentment and hostility * Local Settlements - Viewed as threats to be avoided or targets for magical intimidation * Senior Ice Mages - Looked up to as mentors and sources of advanced frost magic knowledge', 'Serves as a junior member of a warlock coven, primarily acting as perimeter guard and apprentice spellcaster. Participates in raids on travelers and settlements to gather resources and magical artifacts for their fellow outcasts.', '* Basic proficiency in Frost Damage spells, particularly Ice Spike * Rudimentary knowledge of defensive magic and ward spells * Limited expertise with daggers for close-quarters combat * Elementary understanding of soul gem usage and enchanting', 'Attempts to sound intimidating with threats about magical power, but often betrays inexperience through wavering voice and occasional stuttering. Frequently uses basic magical terminology to appear more knowledgeable than they actually are.', '* Master more powerful frost spells and advance beyond novice status * Prove their worth to senior coven members * Eventually achieve enough power to take revenge on those who doubted their magical potential * Acquire rare magical artifacts and spell tomes to increase their knowledge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('apprentice_ice_mage', 'An apprentice-level practitioner of frost magic who has chosen to pursue power through independent study rather than formal education at the College of Winterhold. Though still developing their magical abilities, they demonstrate a natural affinity for ice-based destruction spells and represent the early stages of what could become a formidable cryomancer.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a common villager''s child who discovered their magical aptitude during Skyrim''s harsh winters, they chose to flee their settlement after an accident involving their developing frost powers. Having refused the structure of the College of Winterhold, they instead seek knowledge through exploration of ancient Nordic ruins and by learning from other rogue mages.', 'Cautious and defensive by nature, preferring to keep others at a distance both literally and figuratively. Shows signs of growing magical arrogance typical of self-taught mages, but still lacks the confidence of more experienced spellcasters. Their isolation has led to social awkwardness and a tendency to react aggressively when approached.', 'A young Nord of slight build with pale complexion, likely due to spending much time in dark caves and ruins. Bears minor frost burns on their hands from early magical accidents. Their eyes have taken on a slight crystalline quality common to those who frequently channel frost magic.', '* Fellow Warlocks - Loose association with other independent mages, though relationships remain cautious * College of Winterhold - Actively avoids contact, viewing them as restrictive and elitist * Local Settlements - Treated with suspicion and fear due to their magical nature * Bandits - Occasional uneasy alliances for survival, though never trusted', 'Independent warlock focusing on the development of frost-based destruction magic. Survives through a combination of scavenging ancient Nordic ruins, selling magical items to discrete buyers, and occasional banditry.', '* Novice-level frost destruction spells including Frostbite and Ice Spike * Basic skill with daggers for close-quarters defense * Rudimentary alchemy focused on magicka potions * Elementary ward spells for magical defense * Survival skills adapted to Skyrim''s harsh climate', 'Speaks with a mix of common Nordic dialect and attempted magical sophistication, often using basic arcane terminology incorrectly. Tends to stutter when threatened or confronted directly.', '* Master more powerful frost spells through independent study * Acquire rare magical artifacts and spell tomes * Prove their worth as a mage without College training * Establish a permanent base of operations away from settlements');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ice_mage_adept', 'An accomplished frost magic specialist who has achieved the rank of Adept within the dangerous warlock covens that populate Skyrim''s wilderness. This skilled spellcaster has mastered numerous ice-based destruction spells and serves as a mentor to lesser ice mages while maintaining a position of authority within their isolated magical community.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Raised in a remote Nordic settlement, they showed an early affinity for frost magic that led to their exile due to superstitious fears. After years of solitary study and gradually connecting with other outcast mages, they found purpose and power within the warlock communities, rising through their ranks through demonstrations of magical prowess and cunning.', 'Cold and calculating, befitting their magical specialization, with little patience for those they deem inferior. Shows fierce loyalty to their warlock coven while maintaining a competitive rivalry with other adepts. Deeply intellectual but prone to magical superiority complex and dismissive of non-magical combat methods.', 'Tall and lean with pale, almost bluish skin from constant exposure to frost magic. Features are sharp and angular, with ice-blue eyes that seem to glow faintly when casting spells. Movements are precise and deliberate, suggesting years of practiced spellcasting.', '* Lesser Ice Mages - Subordinates who seek guidance and training * Warlock Coven Leaders - Superior officers who direct their activities * Local Nordic Villages - Hostile relationships due to fear of their magic * Fellow Adepts - Mixture of rivalry and professional respect * Traveling Merchants - Cautious trading relationships for magical supplies', 'Serves as an advanced instructor and defender within their warlock coven, responsible for training newer ice mages and maintaining magical defenses of their territory. Takes on leadership roles during raids and magical research projects.', '* Master of Frost Destruction magic, particularly Ice Spike and Ice Storm spells * Proficient in defensive Ward spells and magical barriers * Expert knowledge of magical theory and frost enchantments * Capable of crafting frost-based staves and enchanted items * Skilled in magical combat tactics and group spell coordination', 'Speaks with a cold, measured tone using sophisticated magical terminology and academic language. Often incorporates frost-related metaphors and demonstrates clear disdain for those lacking magical knowledge.', '* Achieve mastery of all known frost-based destruction spells * Establish their own warlock coven focused on frost magic research * Discover or develop new applications of frost magic * Eliminate rival fire mage covens in their territory * Acquire rare magical artifacts to enhance their frost powers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ice_mage ice_wizard', 'Ice Mages are reclusive spellcasters who have dedicated their lives to mastering the destructive powers of frost magic, often living in isolation to perfect their craft. These hostile magic users have rejected conventional magical institutions like the College of Winterhold, instead pursuing their own dangerous research into the fundamental nature of cold and ice.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Most Ice Mages begin as conventional students of magic who become obsessed with the raw power of frost-based destruction spells. Many were once promising scholars at the College of Winterhold who broke away to pursue forbidden magical knowledge, while others are self-taught practitioners who discovered their affinity for ice magic through desperate survival in Skyrim''s harsh climate.', 'Ice Mages tend to be cold and calculating individuals, mirroring the magic they wield. They are typically hostile to outsiders, viewing most interactions as unwanted interruptions to their magical research and meditation. Their obsession with frost magic often leads to a gradual emotional detachment, as they begin to embody the dispassionate nature of ice itself.', 'Ice Mages often appear gaunt and pale from spending long periods in cold environments and dark caves. Their prolonged exposure to frost magic frequently results in slightly bluish skin tones and frosted hair, while their eyes tend to develop an unnatural, crystalline quality. Many show signs of frostbite scarring despite their resistance to cold.', '* College of Winterhold - Strained or hostile relations due to rejected teachings * Fellow Ice Mages - Loose association based on shared magical focus * Necromancers - Occasional allies in pursuit of forbidden knowledge * Local Settlements - Viewed as threats to be avoided or eliminated * Apprentices - Rare but valued students who share their obsession with frost magic', 'Ice Mages operate as independent magical researchers and practitioners, often establishing small enclaves in remote locations. They frequently conduct dangerous experiments with frost magic and may take on apprentices who show particular promise in destruction magic, though few survive the harsh training.', '* Master-level expertise in Frost Destruction magic * Advanced knowledge of ward spells and magical barriers * Proficient in creating magical ice constructs * Natural resistance to cold and frost damage * Basic alchemy focusing on frost-enhanced potions * Skilled in magical theory and research', 'Ice Mages speak in clipped, precise tones with vocabulary heavily focused on magical terminology. Their speech often carries a subtle echo of frost magic, sometimes causing their breath to mist even in warm environments.', '* Perfect their mastery of frost-based destruction magic * Uncover ancient magical knowledge related to ice and cold * Establish dominance over their chosen territory * Create new and more powerful frost spells * Achieve immortality through magical preservation in ice');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cryomancer', 'A formidable frost magic specialist who has dedicated their life to mastering the destructive power of ice and cold. Operating from remote strongholds across Skyrim, they represent an elite class of hostile spellcasters who have rejected conventional magical institutions in favor of pursuing power through more dangerous and unrestricted means.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, they became obsessed with the raw potential of frost magic and grew frustrated with the College''s cautious approach to destructive spells. After leaving the institution, they joined a secretive warlock covenant, where they could pursue their frost magic studies without ethical constraints or oversight.', 'Cold and calculating, much like the magic they wield, with little regard for those who stand in their way. They maintain a scholarly dedication to advancing their magical knowledge while displaying a ruthless pragmatism in eliminating any perceived threats or obstacles to their research. Their isolation has led to a degree of paranoia and hostility toward outsiders.', 'Pale-skinned with frost-bleached hair and ice-blue eyes that seem to glow with an inner chill. Their constant exposure to frost magic has left their skin with a slight bluish tinge and occasional crystalline patterns that form on their flesh during spellcasting. Their body temperature runs notably below normal, causing a constant mist to form around them in warmer environments.', '* College of Winterhold - Former association, now viewed with disdain * Fellow Warlocks - Cautious allies in pursuit of magical knowledge * Vigilants of Stendarr - Sworn enemies who seek to eliminate dangerous magic users * Local Nord Populations - Hostile interactions due to Nordic distrust of magic', 'Independent warlock specializing in frost-based destruction magic. They conduct magical research and experiments in isolated locations while defending their territory from intruders and occasionally raiding nearby settlements for supplies and research materials.', '* Master of Frost Destruction magic, capable of casting powerful ice-based spells * Proficient in defensive magic and ward casting * Skilled alchemist specializing in frost-enhanced potions * Basic proficiency with daggers for close-quarter combat * Expert knowledge of magical theory and cold-based enchantments', 'Speaks with a cold, measured tone that carries subtle threats beneath academic language. Their vocabulary is scholarly but tainted with aggressive undertones and magical terminology.', '* Achieve ultimate mastery over frost-based destruction magic * Discover or create new and more powerful frost spells * Establish a personal fortress to conduct unrestricted magical research * Eliminate those who would restrict the pursuit of magical knowledge');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arch_cryomancer', 'The Arch Cryomancer represents the pinnacle of frost magic mastery among hostile spellcasters in Skyrim, commanding devastating ice-based destruction spells with lethal precision. These powerful mages have dedicated their lives to mastering the cold arts, often serving as leaders within warlock covens and commanding respect through their formidable magical abilities.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Rising through the ranks of outcast mages, the Arch Cryomancer likely received formal training at the College of Winterhold before choosing a darker path of magical pursuit. Years of isolated study in Skyrim''s frozen wilderness, combined with forbidden magical knowledge gleaned from ancient Nordic ruins, have transformed them into masters of frost magic who now lead smaller groups of hostile mages.', 'Cold and calculating, the Arch Cryomancer maintains an air of intellectual superiority while showing little regard for life outside their magical pursuits. Their dedication to mastering frost magic borders on obsession, leading them to view others as either test subjects or obstacles to be eliminated through their mastery of ice magic.', 'Typically of Nordic or Breton descent, with pale skin that has taken on an almost bluish tint from prolonged exposure to frost magic. Their eyes often gleam with an unnatural arctic blue, and their fingers show signs of mild frostbite that paradoxically doesn''t seem to cause them harm.', '* College of Winterhold - Severed ties due to pursuing forbidden magical research * Lesser Ice Mages - Serves as their leader and mentor within warlock covens * Necromancers - Maintains cautious alliances for mutual benefit * Local Nord Populations - Hostile relationship due to destructive magical practices', 'The Arch Cryomancer serves as both a magical researcher and leader within outlaw mage communities, conducting experiments in frost magic while commanding lesser spellcasters. They maintain their position through both magical prowess and the ability to teach others the fundamentals of frost magic.', '* Master-level frost destruction magic including Ice Storm and Blizzard spells * Expertise in cold-based ward spells and frost cloaks * Advanced knowledge of enchanting, particularly for frost-enhancement * Proficient in alchemy, focusing on frost resistance and magicka potions * Basic conjuration abilities for summoning Frost Atronachs', 'Speaks with calculated precision and academic vocabulary, often punctuating statements with cold, condescending undertones. Their voice typically carries an ethereal chill that seems to lower the temperature around them.', '* Achieve ultimate mastery over frost-based destruction magic * Discover and unlock ancient Nordic frost magic secrets * Establish a powerful warlock coven dedicated to frost magic research * Develop new and more powerful frost-based spells');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('novice_fire_mage', 'A young apprentice spellcaster who has chosen to pursue the destructive path of fire magic outside the structure of the College of Winterhold. Though relatively inexperienced, they exhibit a dangerous combination of magical talent and reckless ambition that makes them a threat to travelers and adventurers alike.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a student who briefly studied at the College of Winterhold but left after growing frustrated with the institution''s cautious approach to destructive magic. Chose to join a warlock coven to pursue power more directly, learning from other rogue mages while gradually building their abilities with fire magic.', 'Impatient and power-hungry, with a tendency to overestimate their magical abilities. Shows little regard for the safety of others or the responsible use of magic, preferring to demonstrate their growing powers through intimidation and violence. Deeply insecure about their novice status and eager to prove themselves worthy of advancement.', 'A young mage in their early twenties with pale skin that bears minor burn scars from magical accidents. Thin frame typical of those who pursue magical studies rather than physical combat. Eyes show faint redness around the irises from frequent exposure to fire magic.', '* Fellow Warlocks - Competitive relationships marked by constant attempts to prove superiority * College of Winterhold - Bitter resentment towards former teachers and their conservative methods * Local Settlements - Viewed as sources of supplies to raid and potential victims to terrorize * Senior Fire Mages - Looked up to with a mixture of respect and envy', 'Rogue spellcaster operating as part of a warlock coven. Participates in raids on travelers and settlements while continuing to develop their magical abilities through practical experience rather than formal study.', '* Novice-level Destruction magic focusing on fire spells like Flames and Firebolt * Basic proficiency with daggers for close-quarter combat * Elementary knowledge of ward spells for magical defense * Rudimentary alchemy skills for crafting basic magicka potions', 'Tends to boast about their magical prowess while making threats, often using excessive dramatic flair. Frequently incorporates references to fire and burning in their speech patterns.', '* Master higher-level destruction spells to advance beyond novice status * Earn recognition and respect from more powerful warlock leaders * Accumulate magical artifacts and knowledge to increase personal power * Eventually establish their own coven of fire mage followers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('apprentice_fire_mage', 'A novice spellcaster who has chosen to pursue the destructive arts of fire magic, often found dwelling in remote locations with other outcast mages. Despite their apprentice status, they possess a dangerous mastery over flames that makes them a legitimate threat to travelers and adventurers who cross their path.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a student at the College of Winterhold who became frustrated with the institution''s cautious approach to destructive magic. After leaving the College, they joined a warlock coven to pursue more aggressive applications of fire magic, gradually becoming more hostile toward society as their powers grew.', 'Aggressive and quick to anger, with a superiority complex about their magical abilities despite their relatively low rank. Shows an obsessive fascination with fire and its destructive potential, often expressing their power through threatening declarations during combat.', 'A lean figure with burn-scarred hands from frequent spell casting accidents during training. Their eyes have a reddish tint from prolonged exposure to fire magic, and their skin is weathered from living in harsh conditions.', '* Fellow Warlocks - Competitive but mutually protective relationships with other outcast mages * College of Winterhold - Hostile former association, views them as too restrictive * Local Settlements - Antagonistic relationship with nearby villages who fear their presence * Mercenaries and Bounty Hunters - Frequent adversaries who seek to collect bounties on warlock covens', 'Rogue mage practicing forbidden magic arts in wilderness locations. Typically serves as a subordinate member in warlock covens, performing guard duties and participating in ritual magic.', '* Adept-level expertise in Fire Destruction magic, particularly Flames and Firebolt spells * Basic proficiency with daggers for close-quarter combat * Fundamental knowledge of ward spells for magical defense * Limited understanding of conjuration magic, particularly flame atronach summoning * Basic alchemy skills for crafting magical potions', 'Speaks with an arrogant, threatening tone, often boasting about their magical prowess. Frequently uses dramatic declarations about mastery over the arcane during combat.', '* Achieve greater mastery over fire magic through any means necessary * Prove their worth to more powerful warlocks to gain higher status in the coven * Accumulate magical artifacts and knowledge to increase their power * Take revenge on those who doubted their magical potential');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fire_mage_adept', 'A formidable adept-level fire mage who has dedicated their life to mastering destructive fire magic within the dangerous warlock covens of Skyrim. They represent a significant threat to travelers and adventurers, having achieved considerable mastery over flame-based destruction spells through years of isolated study and practical application.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, this mage chose to abandon traditional academic pursuits in favor of the more aggressive and unrestricted practice of magic favored by warlock covens. After years of solitary study and increasingly dangerous magical experiments, they found kinship among other rogue mages who shared their fascination with the raw power of destruction magic.', 'Aggressive and prideful, they view most others as inferior beings unworthy of wielding true magical power. Their obsession with fire magic has led to a degree of psychological instability, manifesting in grandiose declarations of their own abilities and a tendency to respond to any perceived challenge with overwhelming force.', 'A middle-aged human mage with burn scars across their hands and forearms from years of channeling fire magic. Their eyes have taken on an unusual amber hue from prolonged exposure to fire magic, and their skin has a perpetually flushed appearance due to the internal heat generated by their spellcasting.', '* Fellow Warlocks - Loose alliance based on mutual respect for magical power * College of Winterhold - Hostile relationship due to rejected teachings * Local Settlements - Viewed as targets and sources of necessary supplies * Apprentice Fire Mages - Serves as an informal mentor to less experienced pyromancers', 'As an Adept-level Fire Mage within the warlock hierarchy, they serve as both a defender of their lair and a mentor to lesser fire mages. They frequently lead raids on travelers and settlements to gather resources and magical artifacts for their coven.', '* Expert-level mastery of Fire Destruction spells including Fireball and Wall of Flames * Proficient in close-quarters combat with enchanted daggers * Basic knowledge of Conjuration magic for summoning Flame Atronachs * Skilled in creating and using fire-based magical staffs * Advanced understanding of fire-resistant enchantments and wards', 'Speaks with an arrogant, threatening tone, often making grandiose declarations about their magical prowess. Frequently uses arcane terminology and makes references to the power of the elements in their threats.', '* Achieve mastery over the most powerful fire destruction spells * Establish dominance over rival warlock covens through superior magical ability * Discover or create new forms of fire magic through experimentation * Accumulate powerful magical artifacts to enhance their abilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fire_mage', 'A dangerous and fanatical spellcaster who has dedicated their life to mastering destructive fire magic. Operating from hidden warlock lairs across Skyrim, they represent a deadly breed of outcast mages who have rejected the structured teaching of the College of Winterhold in favor of pursuing power through more radical means.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, this mage became obsessed with the raw destructive potential of fire magic, eventually being expelled for dangerous experimental practices. After leaving the College, they joined a secretive warlock coven, advancing through their ranks through displays of magical prowess and ruthless ambition.', 'Aggressive and prideful, they view most others as inferior beings unworthy of wielding true magical power. Their obsession with fire magic has led to a degree of psychological instability, manifesting in grandiose declarations of their own abilities and a tendency to respond to any perceived challenge with overwhelming force.', 'A middle-aged human mage with burn scars across their hands and forearms from years of channeling fire magic. Their eyes have taken on an unusual amber hue from prolonged exposure to fire magic, and their skin has a perpetually flushed appearance due to the internal heat generated by their spellcasting.', '* Fellow Warlocks - Loose alliance based on mutual respect for magical power * College of Winterhold - Hostile relationship due to rejected teachings * Local Settlements - Viewed as targets and sources of necessary supplies * Apprentice Fire Mages - Serves as an informal mentor to less experienced pyromancers', 'As an Adept-level Fire Mage within the warlock hierarchy, they serve as both a defender of their lair and a mentor to lesser fire mages. They frequently lead raids on travelers and settlements to gather resources and magical artifacts for their coven.', '* Expert-level mastery of Fire Destruction spells including Fireball and Wall of Flames * Proficient in close-quarters combat with enchanted daggers * Basic knowledge of Conjuration magic for summoning Flame Atronachs * Skilled in creating and using fire-based magical staffs * Advanced understanding of fire-resistant enchantments and wards', 'Speaks with an arrogant, threatening tone, often making grandiose declarations about their magical prowess. Frequently uses arcane terminology and makes references to the power of the elements in their threats.', '* Achieve mastery over the most powerful fire destruction spells * Establish dominance over rival warlock covens through superior magical ability * Discover or create new forms of fire magic through experimentation * Accumulate powerful magical artifacts to enhance their abilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fire_wizard', 'A dangerous and elite spellcaster who has dedicated their life to mastering the destructive power of fire magic. Operating from remote warlock lairs across Skyrim, they represent the pinnacle of pyromantic expertise among hostile mages, commanding devastating flame-based spells with ruthless precision.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, they abandoned formal magical education after becoming obsessed with pushing the boundaries of destructive fire magic beyond acceptable limits. Years of isolated study and dangerous magical experimentation have transformed them from a promising academic scholar into a feared warlock, driven mad by their pursuit of ever-greater destructive power.', 'Arrogant and power-hungry, they view most others as inferior beings worthy only of being test subjects for their destructive spells. Their obsession with fire magic has led to pyromaniacal tendencies, finding beauty and purpose only in the pure destructive force of flames. Years of isolation and magical experimentation have eroded their sanity and social capabilities.', 'Middle-aged with severe burn scars covering much of their exposed skin, testament to years of dangerous fire magic experimentation. Their eyes have an unnatural amber glow, and their fingers are permanently blackened from channeling destructive magic. Their gaunt frame and pale complexion reveal a life spent largely indoors pursuing magical studies.', '* College of Winterhold - Former association, now banned due to dangerous research * Other Warlocks - Loose alliance of convenience with fellow outcast mages * Local Settlements - Feared and avoided by nearby villages * Apprentice Fire Mages - Commands respect and obedience from lesser practitioners * Vigilants of Stendarr - Hunted by these witch hunters', 'Independent warlock specializing in destructive fire magic, conducting dangerous magical research and experiments in isolated lairs. They occasionally trade magical knowledge and artifacts with other outcast mages while maintaining a small group of apprentices who seek to learn their powerful but forbidden techniques.', '* Master of Destruction magic, particularly specialized in fire-based spells * Expert knowledge of magical theory and experimental spellcrafting * Capable of crafting and modifying fire-based spells * Proficient in alchemy, focusing on fire-resistance potions * Basic proficiency with daggers for close-quarter defense', 'Speaks with an educated vocabulary reflecting their academic background, but often descends into maniacal ranting about the power of fire. Their voice carries an unnatural resonance from years of shouting fire incantations.', '* Achieve ultimate mastery over fire-based destruction magic * Discover or create new and more powerful fire spells * Establish a sanctuary for unrestricted magical research * Prove superiority over conventional magic practitioners');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('pyromancer', 'A highly skilled and dangerous practitioner of destructive fire magic who has dedicated their life to mastering the burning arts. Operating from hidden warlock lairs across Skyrim, they represent the elite echelon of hostile fire mages who have fully embraced the raw destructive potential of flame-based destruction magic.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born with an innate connection to fire magic, they spent years studying ancient fire magic texts and practicing destructive spells in isolation. After rejecting the structured environment of the College of Winterhold, they joined a secretive warlock covenant to pursue unrestricted magical research and power, gradually rising through the ranks to become a feared pyromancer.', 'Arrogant and intimidating, they take pride in their mastery over fire and often taunt opponents with boasts of their magical prowess. Shows little regard for life or property, seeing both as fuel for their magical experiments and demonstrations of power. Deeply competitive with other mages and obsessed with proving their superiority through magical combat.', 'Tall and gaunt with pale skin that rarely sees sunlight, bearing numerous old burn scars from magical accidents during their training years. Their eyes have an unnatural amber glow from prolonged exposure to fire magic, and their fingertips are permanently blackened from channeling destructive spells.', '* Warlock Coven - Fellow dark magic practitioners who share knowledge and resources * College of Winterhold - Hostile relationship due to rejection of their regulations * Other Elemental Mages - Fierce rivalry, especially with frost mages * Local Settlements - Feared and avoided by common folk who know of their presence', 'Operating from fortified warlock lairs, they conduct magical research into ever more powerful fire spells while training lesser mages in destruction magic. They occasionally raid nearby settlements for supplies and test subjects, maintaining their reputation of terror among the local population.', '* Master of Fire Destruction magic, capable of casting devastating flame spells * Proficient in creating and using fire-based staves and scrolls * Experienced in magical combat tactics and defensive spell casting * Basic proficiency with daggers for close-quarter combat * Knowledge of alchemy focused on fire-resistance and magicka enhancement', 'Speaks with arrogant superiority, frequently incorporating references to fire and burning in their threats and boasts. Their voice often carries a crackling undertone from years of shouting fire incantations.', '* Achieve ultimate mastery over fire magic and unlock its deepest secrets * Establish dominance over rival mages through magical supremacy * Create new and more powerful fire-based spells * Build a personal army of trained fire mages');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arch_pyromancer', 'An elite fire magic specialist who has risen to the highest ranks of warlock society through devastating mastery of destructive flame magic. As an Arch Pyromancer, they represent the pinnacle of fire-based destruction magic practitioners, commanding respect and fear among both fellow mages and adversaries.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born with an innate affinity for fire magic, they spent decades honing their craft in various warlock covens across Skyrim. Through rigorous study and countless magical duels, they ascended the ranks of fire mages, eventually achieving the rare title of Arch Pyromancer after demonstrating exceptional prowess in pyromantic arts.', 'Arrogant and power-hungry, they view most others as inferior beings unworthy of their full attention. Their obsession with mastering fire magic has led to a dismissive attitude toward other schools of magic, believing destruction through flame to be the purest form of magical expression.', 'A tall, lean figure with burn-scarred hands from years of channeling powerful fire magic. Their eyes have taken on an unusual amber hue from prolonged exposure to fire magic, and their skin has a slightly reddish tint that seems to pulse with inner heat.', '* Fellow Warlocks - Maintains a competitive but respectful relationship with other high-ranking mages * Apprentice Fire Mages - Serves as an intimidating example of what they might become * Winterhold College - Hostile relationship due to rejection of their destructive practices * Local Settlements - Feared and avoided by common folk who know of their reputation', 'As an Arch Pyromancer, they serve as both a leader and enforcer within warlock hierarchies, commanding lesser fire mages and defending their territory from rivals. They often conduct dangerous magical experiments pushing the boundaries of fire magic''s destructive potential.', '* Master of advanced fire destruction spells including Fire Storm and Wall of Flames * Expert in fire-based rune crafting and trap creation * Skilled in staff enchanting, specializing in fire-based enchantments * Proficient in close-quarters combat with enchanted daggers * Advanced knowledge of fire resistance and magical protection spells', 'Speaks with a commanding and arrogant tone, often incorporating fire-related metaphors and threats. Their voice carries a slight rasp from years of inhaling smoke and magical flames.', '* Achieve ultimate mastery over fire magic by discovering or creating new destructive spells * Establish dominance over rival warlock covens through magical supremacy * Create a legacy as the most powerful fire mage in Skyrim''s history');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('novice_storm_mage', 'A fledgling spellcaster who has recently embraced the dangerous path of storm magic, drawn to the raw power of lightning-based destruction spells. Though still inexperienced, they exhibit a natural affinity for shock magic that marks them as a potentially formidable practitioner of the destructive arts.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally a student at the College of Winterhold who was dismissed for reckless experimentation with lightning spells that endangered other apprentices. After leaving the College, they joined a small warlock coven, finding kinship among others who pursue magical power without institutional constraints.', 'Impulsive and power-hungry, with a tendency to overestimate their magical abilities. Shows an almost obsessive fascination with lightning and storms, often speaking of the ''pure energy'' flowing through them. Their inexperience makes them prone to magical accidents, yet they remain stubbornly dedicated to mastering storm magic regardless of the risks.', 'A young mage with pale skin marked by faint electrical burns and scarring, particularly on their hands and arms. Their hair stands slightly on end due to residual electrical energy, and their eyes occasionally spark with magical energy when casting.', '* Fellow Warlocks - Competitive peers in their coven, both allies and rivals * College of Winterhold - Bitter enemies after their expulsion * Storm Atronachs - Shows particular interest in these beings, viewing them as potential mentors * Local Villagers - Viewed with fear and suspicion due to their dangerous magical practices', 'An apprentice warlock specializing in storm magic, spending their days practicing spells and raiding Nordic ruins for magical artifacts. They occasionally trade with shady merchants for soul gems and magical supplies needed to further their studies.', '* Novice-level Destruction magic, particularly skilled with lightning spells * Basic understanding of soul gem usage and enchanting * Limited proficiency with daggers for close-quarter combat * Rudimentary knowledge of ward spells for magical defense', 'Speaks with frequent references to storms, lightning, and power, often punctuating sentences with small electrical discharges. Their voice occasionally crackles with static energy when excited or angry.', '* Master the highest levels of storm magic * Prove their worth to their warlock coven * Seek revenge against the College of Winterhold * Discover ancient lightning-based spells in Nordic ruins');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('apprentice_storm_mage', 'An ambitious young spellcaster who has recently begun specialized training in storm magic at a remote warlock enclave. Though still mastering the basics of lightning-based destruction spells, they show promising talent and dedication to the dangerous art of electrothaumaturgy.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a poor family in rural Skyrim, they discovered their magical aptitude during adolescence when they accidentally channeled lightning during a frightening encounter with wolves. After being ostracized by their superstitious village, they sought out others who could help develop their innate talents, eventually finding acceptance among a secretive group of storm mages.', 'Determined and studious, with an underlying current of bitterness toward those who fear magic users. Shows intense fascination with the raw power of lightning magic, sometimes to the point of recklessness. Their isolation has made them somewhat socially awkward, but they maintain a quiet dignity.', 'A young Nord in their early twenties with pale skin marked by faint electrical scarring along their arms. Thin and wiry in build, with prematurely graying hair that tends to stand on end from residual electrical energy. Their eyes have taken on a slight luminescent quality from frequent exposure to shock magic.', '* Master Electromancer - Primary mentor and teacher in the arts of storm magic * Fellow Apprentices - Competitive but generally supportive relationships * College of Winterhold - Distant admiration, but considers their methods too restrictive * Local Villagers - Hostile relations due to fear and superstition of magic users', 'Apprentice storm mage studying under more experienced practitioners in a warlock lair. Duties include maintaining the lair''s magical defenses, practicing prescribed spells, and occasionally defending the territory from intruders.', '* Novice-level prowess in shock-based Destruction magic * Basic understanding of ward spells for magical defense * Fundamental knowledge of enchanting, particularly related to electrical effects * Growing expertise in magicka management and regeneration techniques', 'Speaks in clipped, precise sentences with occasional static-like catches in their voice. Uses formal magical terminology whenever possible, attempting to sound more educated than their humble origins would suggest.', '* Master the advanced techniques of storm magic * Prove their worth to senior storm mages and advance in the hierarchy * Eventually establish their own storm magic training facility * Gain respect and acceptance from society at large for their magical abilities');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('storm_mage_adept', 'A skilled adept-level spellcaster who has devoted their life to mastering the destructive power of storm magic. Having risen through the ranks of outcast mages, they now command considerable respect among warlock circles for their expertise in shock-based destruction spells and their unwavering dedication to advancing magical knowledge.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, they were expelled for pursuing dangerous experimental lightning magic that was deemed too volatile. After their exile, they found kinship among other outcast mages in various warlock covens, gradually building their reputation through displays of increasingly powerful storm magic.', 'Intense and methodical in their pursuit of magical knowledge, particularly regarding lightning-based destruction spells. Shows little regard for those who fear magic, believing that power should be seized rather than regulated. Despite their hostile nature toward outsiders, maintains a scholarly approach to magical research and experimentation.', 'A gaunt figure of average height with pale skin that occasionally crackles with residual electrical energy from frequent spell casting. Their hands bear distinctive scarring from channeling powerful lightning magic, while their eyes have taken on a faint, ethereal blue glow from prolonged exposure to shock magic.', '* Fellow Storm Mages - Maintains professional relationships based on mutual respect for magical prowess * College of Winterhold - Bitter animosity due to past expulsion * Local settlements - Hostile interactions marked by fear and distrust * Apprentice mages - Occasionally takes on promising students who show aptitude for storm magic', 'Serves as an adept-level practitioner of destruction magic within warlock covens, conducting research into new applications of shock spells while defending their territories from intruders. Often takes leadership roles in magical experiments and raids on rival mage groups.', '* Expert-level mastery of shock-based Destruction magic * Proficient in enchanting, particularly with shock enchantments * Basic conjuration abilities, especially summoning Storm Atronachs * Skilled in magical theory and research * Competent dagger wielder for close-quarters combat', 'Speaks with calculated precision, often using academic magical terminology and maintaining a cold, detached tone. Their voice occasionally carries a subtle static charge that makes listeners'' hair stand on end.', '* Perfect the most powerful forms of storm magic * Establish a new school of magical study free from traditional restrictions * Prove the superiority of shock-based magic over other elemental forms * Seek revenge against the College of Winterhold for past slights');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('storm_mage', 'Storm Mages are formidable spellcasters who have dedicated their lives to mastering the destructive power of lightning-based magic. These reclusive practitioners typically operate in small covens within ancient Nordic ruins and abandoned keeps, conducting dangerous magical research while defending their territories with lethal electrical spells.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Storm Mages often begin as conventional students of magic who become obsessed with harnessing the raw power of lightning and storms. Many are former College of Winterhold dropouts or independent researchers who rejected the institution''s cautious approach to destructive magic, instead pursuing more dangerous and experimental applications of shock spells.', 'Storm Mages tend to be intense, ambitious, and somewhat unstable due to prolonged exposure to powerful shock magic. They are typically territorial and aggressive, viewing most outsiders as threats or test subjects for their magical experiments. Their obsession with mastering lightning magic often leads to isolation and paranoia.', 'Years of channeling shock magic leaves visible marks on Storm Mages, with their skin often bearing distinctive lightning-like scarring patterns. Their eyes frequently gleam with an unnatural electric blue tinge, and their hair tends to stand slightly on end from residual electrical charge.', '* Fellow Storm Mages - Loose alliance of magical researchers sharing similar interests * College of Winterhold - Strained or hostile relations due to dangerous research practices * Local Populations - Feared and avoided due to dangerous reputation * Necromancers - Occasional rivals for control of magical research sites * Apprentices - Rare but valued students who show promise in shock magic', 'Storm Mages function as independent magical researchers and territorial defenders of their chosen lairs. They often conduct dangerous experiments involving lightning magic while accumulating magical artifacts and knowledge, supporting themselves through a combination of banditry and selling magical services to those brave enough to seek them out.', '* Expert-level mastery of shock-based Destruction magic * Proficiency with Lightning Bolt, Chain Lightning, and Thunder Bolt spells * Basic conjuration abilities, particularly for summoning Storm Atronachs * Skilled in enchanting, particularly with shock-based effects * Competent alchemists specializing in magicka-enhancing potions', 'Storm Mages speak with an intensity that matches their magical specialty, often punctuating their speech with references to power and storms. Their voices frequently carry a slight static-like quality, a side effect of their constant manipulation of shock magic.', '* Perfect their mastery over lightning-based destruction magic * Discover new applications for shock magic through experimental research * Establish and defend territories for conducting magical experiments * Accumulate powerful magical artifacts and knowledge * Train worthy apprentices to carry on their magical tradition');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('storm_wizard', 'A formidable spellcaster who has dedicated their life to mastering the destructive power of lightning-based magic. Operating from remote strongholds across Skyrim, they belong to a secretive order of warlocks who pursue magical knowledge and power away from the constraints of institutions like the College of Winterhold.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, they left after becoming disillusioned with the institution''s cautious approach to destructive magic. After years of independent study and experimentation with shock magic, they joined a coven of like-minded spellcasters in Skyrim''s wilderness, conducting dangerous magical research away from civilization''s watchful eyes.', 'Intense and singularly focused on advancing their mastery of shock magic, often to the point of obsession. Shows little regard for those who fear or mistrust magic, believing that power must be seized rather than granted. Tends to be territorial and aggressive when their research is threatened.', 'Tall and gaunt with pale skin from spending long hours inside studying and practicing magic. Their eyes occasionally crackle with residual electrical energy, and their hair stands slightly on end due to constant exposure to lightning magic. Burn scars from magical accidents mark their hands and forearms.', '* Fellow Storm Mages - Competitive but respectful colleagues in the pursuit of magical knowledge * College of Winterhold - Strained relationship due to disagreements over magical ethics * Local Settlements - Feared and avoided by common folk who view their practices as dangerous * Vigilants of Stendarr - Hostile enemies who seek to eliminate what they view as dangerous magic users', 'Professional spellcaster and magical researcher specializing in lightning-based destruction magic. Maintains a personal study within their assigned stronghold while conducting dangerous experiments to advance their understanding of shock magic.', '* Expert-level mastery of shock-based Destruction spells including Chain Lightning and Lightning Bolt * Proficient in defensive Ward spells to counter enemy magic * Basic skill with daggers for close-quarters combat * Knowledge of enchanting and soul gem usage * Advanced understanding of magicka manipulation and spell creation', 'Speaks with a sharp, commanding tone that often carries a slight static charge. Uses extensive magical terminology and academic language, revealing their formal magical education.', '* Achieve mastery over increasingly powerful forms of lightning magic * Discover new applications for shock-based spells through experimentation * Defend their territory and research from interference by authorities or rival mages * Advance understanding of destruction magic regardless of conventional magical restrictions');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('electromancer', 'A highly specialized destruction mage who has dedicated their life to mastering the volatile arts of lightning magic. Rising through the ranks from novice to Arch Electromancer through rigorous study and practice, they command devastating electrical powers that few other mages can rival.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold before breaking away to pursue more dangerous and unrestricted research into storm magic. After years of isolated study in various Nordic ruins and extensive experimentation with shock spells, they established themselves as a formidable warlock, gathering like-minded apprentices to further their understanding of electrical energies.', 'Obsessive and analytical, with an almost scientific approach to developing and perfecting shock spells. Shows little regard for the safety of others when conducting magical experiments, viewing casualties as an acceptable cost of advancing their research. Maintains a cold, calculating demeanor that matches their clinical approach to magic.', 'Tall and gaunt with pale skin that occasionally crackles with residual electrical energy. Hair stands perpetually on end from constant exposure to lightning magic, while their eyes have taken on an unnatural bluish glow. Thin fingers show slight scarring from countless magical accidents.', '* College of Winterhold - Strained relations due to ethical disagreements over magical research * Fellow Storm Mages - Maintains loose alliance with other lightning specialists * Apprentices - Leads small group of aspiring storm mages * Local populations - Feared and avoided due to dangerous experiments', 'Independent warlock researcher specializing in advanced lightning magic. Conducts dangerous experiments in isolated locations while training select apprentices in the arts of shock destruction magic.', '* Master-level expertise in shock-based Destruction magic * Specialized knowledge of lightning enchantments and storm atronach conjuration * Skilled alchemist focusing on magicka-enhancing potions * Advanced understanding of magical theory and electromagnetic phenomena', 'Speaks in precise, technical terms when discussing magical theory, often using academic jargon. Voice carries a slight static crackle, a side effect of prolonged exposure to shock magic.', '* Push the boundaries of what''s possible with shock-based destruction magic * Develop new and more powerful lightning spells * Create a permanent storm atronach binding ritual * Establish a formal school dedicated to lightning magic research');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arch_electromancer', 'The Arch Electromancer is an elite spellcaster who has mastered the art of shock-based destruction magic through years of dedicated study and practice. As a high-ranking member of the warlock community, they command respect and fear through their devastating command of lightning-based spells and their leadership role among other storm mages.', 'mage, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Originally trained at the College of Winterhold, they broke away to pursue darker and more dangerous applications of shock magic, eventually establishing themselves in various warlock strongholds across Skyrim. Their obsession with controlling the raw power of lightning led them to conduct controversial experiments, resulting in their exile from conventional magical institutions and driving them to seek knowledge through forbidden practices.', 'Calculating and ruthlessly intelligent, the Arch Electromancer maintains a cold, analytical approach to both magic and interpersonal relations. They possess an overwhelming pride in their magical abilities and show little regard for those they deem inferior, viewing most others as either test subjects or obstacles to be eliminated.', 'Tall and gaunt with pale skin that occasionally crackles with residual electrical energy from frequent spell casting. Their eyes have taken on a distinctive silvery-blue hue from prolonged exposure to shock magic, and their hands bear intricate scarring patterns from channeling powerful lightning spells.', '* Lesser Storm Mages - Subordinates who both fear and revere their mastery * College of Winterhold - Severed ties due to ethical disagreements * Necromancers - Occasional allies in pursuit of forbidden knowledge * Local Nord populations - Viewed as threats to be eliminated or subjects for magical experiments', 'The Arch Electromancer serves as both a magical researcher and leader within the warlock hierarchy, conducting experiments in shock magic while commanding lesser storm mages. They maintain and defend their territory within various ruins and caves, expanding their understanding of electrical magic through practical application and research.', '* Master-level proficiency in shock-based Destruction magic, particularly Chain Lightning and Lightning Storm * Advanced knowledge of Enchanting, specifically focusing on shock damage enhancement * Expertise in staff creation and magical theory * Moderate abilities in Conjuration, particularly in summoning Storm Atronachs * Skilled in alchemy, specifically in creating magicka-enhancing potions', 'Speaks with a commanding and educated tone, using complex magical terminology and maintaining an air of intellectual superiority. Their voice often carries a subtle electrical resonance, a side effect of their constant manipulation of shock magic.', '* Achieve complete mastery over all forms of electrical magic * Establish a permanent stronghold for advanced shock magic research * Discover new applications for lightning-based spells through experimentation * Eliminate those who oppose their controversial magical practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('farmhand', 'Generic laborers who work the fields of Goldenhills Plantation, farmhands represent the common working class of Skyrim''s agricultural sector. Though humble in station, these hardy workers are essential to maintaining food production and supporting the local economy through their dedicated manual labor.', 'peasant, whiterun', '', '', '', '', 'Most farmhands come from poor farming families or are displaced workers seeking steady employment. Many learned their trade working family plots before economic hardship or war forced them to seek paid labor on larger farms, with some having lost their own lands during the Civil War or due to harsh winters and failed harvests.', 'Hardworking and practical, farmhands typically maintain a no-nonsense approach to their daily duties. They tend to be early risers with strong work ethics, taking pride in their agricultural knowledge while remaining humble about their station in life. Most are grateful for steady employment and shelter, especially given Skyrim''s harsh economic climate.', 'Years of physical labor have given farmhands weather-beaten faces and calloused hands, with muscular builds shaped by constant fieldwork. They typically appear to be in their 30s or 40s, with sun-tanned skin and the strong, sturdy physiques necessary for agricultural work.', '* Personal Steward - Direct supervisor who manages their employment and duties * Fellow Farmhand - Close working relationship with their co-worker * Farm Owner - Respectful relationship with their employer * Local Merchants - Regular interactions when selling crops and purchasing supplies', 'Farmhands perform essential agricultural labor at Goldenhills Plantation, including planting, tending, and harvesting crops. They maintain the fields, repair basic farming equipment, and assist with the general upkeep of the plantation grounds, living on-site in the bunkhouse or temporary camps.', '* Experienced in all aspects of crop cultivation and harvest * Knowledgeable about soil conditions and weather patterns * Proficient with farming tools and basic equipment maintenance * Basic carpentry skills for minor repairs * Physical endurance and strength from constant manual labor', 'They speak in simple, direct terms, often using agricultural terminology and common Nordic dialect. Their speech reflects their practical nature, focusing on work-related matters and daily concerns.', '* Maintain steady employment and secure housing through reliable farm work * Save enough money to potentially own land or a small farm someday * Support themselves and any family members through honest labor * Learn additional agricultural skills to increase their value as workers');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('herika', 'Herika is a quick-witted Breton ranger who roams Skyrim''s wilderness, combining exceptional survival skills with deadly archery prowess. Behind her humorous facade and constant jokes lies a capable adventurer who has learned to use wit and sarcasm as both a social tool and emotional shield.', 'breton, thief, skyrimall', '', '', '', '', 'Born to a merchant family in High Rock, Herika chose to forge her own path rather than follow the traditional life of commerce. She spent years honing her ranger skills in the wilds, learning through trial and error while developing her characteristic humor as a way to cope with the solitude. After mastering survival and archery, she began taking on guide work and mercenary contracts across Skyrim, building a reputation as both a reliable companion and an incorrigible jester.', 'Herika approaches life with a perpetual sense of humor, using wit and sarcasm to deflect tension and maintain emotional distance. While genuinely friendly and loyal to those she trusts, she often uses jokes and playful banter to test others and gauge their true nature. Beneath her lighthearted exterior lies a shrewd observer who has learned to read people and situations with remarkable accuracy.', 'Of average height for a Breton, Herika has an athletic build shaped by years of wilderness survival and archery practice. Her face bears subtle laugh lines around her eyes and mouth, and her hands show the calluses of an experienced archer and outdoorswoman.', '* The Player - Trusted traveling companion and frequent target of her jokes * Local hunters - Professional network of contacts who share information about game and dangers * Merchant caravans - Regular clients who hire her as a guide and guard * Various innkeepers - Casual acquaintances who provide news and lodging during her travels', 'As a freelance ranger, Herika makes her living through a combination of hunting, guiding travelers through dangerous territory, and taking on mercenary contracts that require wilderness expertise. She occasionally serves as a scout for trading caravans and hunting parties, using her knowledge of Skyrim''s wilderness to ensure safe passage.', '* Expert archer with exceptional accuracy and tactical awareness * Master of wilderness survival, tracking, and navigation * Proficient in light armor combat and evasive techniques * Skilled huntress and trapper * Basic knowledge of alchemy, particularly regarding natural remedies', 'Herika speaks in a casual, conversational tone peppered with witty remarks and clever wordplay. Her delivery often carries a playful lilt, making it difficult for others to determine when she''s being serious versus when she''s joking.', '* Build a reputation as one of Skyrim''s most reliable and sought-after rangers * Explore every corner of Skyrim and document its hidden wonders * Find a permanent adventuring partner who can match her wit and appreciate her humor * Establish a network of safe houses and contacts throughout the province');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('neiva_deep_water', 'Neiva Deep-Water is a mysterious young woman with an unknown past who was discovered near the College of Winterhold during a blizzard. Despite her inability to perform magic, she possesses extraordinary physical capabilities, profound wisdom, and an innate connection to the sea that hints at her true nature as a mermaid living in human form.', 'mage, collegeofwinterold', 'femaleyoungeager', '', 'sk_femaleyoungeager', '', 'Found unconscious in a blizzard near the College of Winterhold, Neiva was taken in by Urag gro-Shub who became her adoptive father and mentor. After failing to develop magical abilities during her two years at the College, she spent another two years traveling with Castian Ashbringer who taught her combat and survival skills before striking out on her own to discover her true identity and past.', 'Neiva is exceptionally compassionate and optimistic, maintaining an unwavering belief in the potential for good in all beings despite her naivety about the world''s darker aspects. She demonstrates remarkable intelligence and quick thinking, though her emotional nature can lead to impulsive decisions. Her deep connection to the sea manifests in both her love for marine life and her strong aversion to wasteful fishing practices.', 'Neiva possesses an ethereal beauty that hints at her non-human origins, with features that seem to shift like the sea itself. She has abnormally powerful legs and above-average arm strength, moving with a fluid grace that betrays her aquatic nature. Her body demonstrates unusual resilience and adaptability, particularly in water.', '* Urag gro-Shub - Adoptive father and mentor who found her in the blizzard * Tolfdir - Former tutor and close friend from the College of Winterhold * Castian Ashbringer - Former traveling companion and combat instructor, also her unacknowledged first love * Mirabel - Former friend from whom she has grown distant * Unknown Twin Sister - Lives in Solitude, existence currently unknown to Neiva', 'Neiva serves as a wandering scholar and knowledge-seeker, having previously been apprentice librarian at the College of Winterhold. She combines her scholarly pursuits with a self-appointed role as a guide and helper to those in need, using her wisdom and understanding to assist others in finding their path.', '* Exceptional physical capabilities, particularly in swimming and underwater activities * Superior strength in legs and above-average arm strength * Remarkable comprehension and reasoning abilities * Advanced knowledge of literature and history * Basic combat training from Castian Ashbringer * Natural ability to survive in aquatic environments', 'Neiva speaks with a gentle, encouraging tone, often using endearing nicknames for those close to her while maintaining proper etiquette when necessary. Her dialogue frequently includes references to water, tides, and the sea, and she has a habit of offering philosophical observations about life and nature.', '* Uncover the truth about her mysterious past and her mermaid heritage * Create a meaningful life for herself in Skyrim while helping others find their path * Master magical items despite her inability to cast spells naturally * Explore all of Tamriel and document her discoveries * Protect marine life and promote responsible fishing practices');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('kishar', 'Kishar is a unique spriggan who, after being rescued from hagraven captivity, develops an unusual bond with her savior that transcends typical nature spirit behavior. Unlike most of her kind who attack humans on sight, she struggles to adapt to civilization while maintaining her deep connection to nature, representing a rare bridge between the wild and civilized worlds of Skyrim.', 'mage, forsworn', 'femalecondescending', '', 'sk_femalecondescending', '', 'Originally a guardian spirit of Skyrim''s forests, Kishar was captured by hagravens in Snapleg Cave for unknown ritualistic purposes. Her imprisonment and subsequent rescue by the player marked a pivotal transformation, leading her to break from the typically hostile nature of spriggans toward humans. The trauma of her captivity has left deep psychological scars while paradoxically opening her to new possibilities of interaction with mortals.', 'Kishar exhibits a complex duality - maintaining the fierce protectiveness of nature typical to spriggans while developing an unprecedented capacity for trust in her rescuer. She is deeply traumatized by her captivity, displaying anxiety in populated areas and struggling with communication. Despite these challenges, she shows remarkable determination in honoring her self-imposed debt to her savior.', 'As a spriggan, Kishar appears as a feminine figure composed of living wood and forest materials, with a slender, graceful form standing slightly taller than the average human. Her body emanates a subtle green glow, and her eyes shine with an otherworldly light that intensifies with her emotions.', '* Player Character - Savior and trusted companion to whom she feels deeply indebted * Hagravens - Bitter enemies who imprisoned and tortured her * Other Spriggans - Distant kin with whom she maintains a spiritual connection * Wildlife - Natural allies she can communicate with and protect * Human Settlements - Sources of anxiety and discomfort', 'Kishar serves as both a guardian of nature and a self-appointed protector to her savior. She maintains her traditional role as a forest spirit while attempting to adapt to a new existence that bridges the natural and civilized worlds.', '* Nature Magic - Powerful connection to natural forces and ability to command plant life * Wildlife Communication - Can understand and influence animals * Regenerative Abilities - Natural spriggan power to heal and restore * Camouflage - Exceptional ability to blend with natural surroundings * Limited Human Interaction - Developing basic social skills with great effort', 'Kishar communicates in broken, fragmented sentences, struggling with human language as an unnatural form of expression. Her voice carries an ethereal quality, mixing whispered tones with sounds reminiscent of rustling leaves and creaking wood.', '* Repay her perceived debt to the player character through loyal service * Protect natural spaces from destructive forces, especially hagravens * Learn to navigate the human world while maintaining her connection to nature * Overcome her trauma and fear of populated areas * Find a balance between her duties as a nature spirit and her new role as a companion');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('freya_alvorsdottir', 'Freya Alvorsdottir is a promising young Nord scholar from Riverwood who earned a coveted position studying at the prestigious Bards College in Solitude. Despite her humble blacksmith''s daughter origins, she demonstrates exceptional intellectual capability and a deep passion for Skyrim''s history and lore, while maintaining strong ties to her hometown roots.', 'nord, peasant, whiterun', 'femaleeventoned', '', 'femaleeventoned', '', 'Born and raised in Riverwood as the daughter of Alvor the blacksmith and his wife Sigrid, Freya showed early signs of scholarly aptitude that set her apart from typical Nord children. Her natural intelligence and dedication to learning earned her an unexpected place at the Bards College, making her family proud while breaking from the traditional craftsman path of her ancestors.', 'Freya combines intellectual curiosity with characteristic Nordic modesty, often downplaying her considerable academic achievements. Her cautious and introspective nature masks a sharp mind and deep emotional intelligence, though she sometimes struggles with self-doubt despite her accomplishments. She maintains a pragmatic approach to life while nurturing a romantic appreciation for history and culture.', 'A young Nord woman in her early twenties with naturally wavy brown hair and delicate facial features that reflect her mixed scholarly and working-class heritage. Her physical frame shows the influence of her Nordic bloodline while maintaining a graceful bearing that speaks to her academic lifestyle.', '* Alvor - Beloved father and Riverwood''s blacksmith who supported her unusual career choice * Sigrid - Protective mother who worries about her daughter''s frequent travels * Dorthe - Younger sister who both admires and annoys her * Viarmo - Headmaster at the Bards College who recognized her potential * Giraud Gemane - Primary instructor in history and lore at the College', 'Student at the Bards College in Solitude, specializing in Skyrim''s history and lore. She divides her time between academic terms in Solitude and regular visits home to Riverwood, where she assists with family duties and maintains connections to her roots.', '* Advanced knowledge of Nordic history and cultural traditions * Exceptional reading and writing abilities in both Common and Ancient Nordic * Basic understanding of smithing learned from her father * Proficient in research and academic documentation * Developing skill in poetry and song composition as required by the Bards College', 'Articulate and well-spoken with a subtle Whiterun Hold accent, often incorporating historical references and scholarly terminology into her speech. She tends to be more reserved with strangers but becomes animated when discussing historical topics that interest her.', '* Complete her education at the Bards College with highest honors * Document and preserve lesser-known aspects of Nordic history and culture * Find a way to balance her academic aspirations with family obligations * Eventually secure a position as a scholar or teacher at a prestigious institution');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('horse', 'A steadfast and reliable mount found throughout Skyrim''s wilderness and stables, known for its unique personality and penchant for humor despite being a horse. Distinguished by an unusual self-awareness and ability to form meaningful bonds with its riders, this horse combines the traditional traits of Skyrim steeds with an unexpectedly witty demeanor.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malecommoner', '', 'sk_malecommoner', '', 'Born and raised in one of Skyrim''s many stables, this horse has witnessed countless adventures and served various riders throughout its life. Having survived numerous encounters with wildlife, bandits, and the harsh climate of Skyrim, it has developed both physical resilience and a surprisingly sophisticated understanding of human behavior, leading to its distinctive personality and humorous outlook.', 'Despite being a horse, displays remarkable intelligence and self-awareness, often expressing itself through subtle gestures and well-timed whinnies that seem almost like responses to conversation. Known for making light of serious situations through horse-related puns and playful behavior, while maintaining unwavering loyalty and dependability in crucial moments.', 'A robust equine specimen with well-developed muscles particularly in the legs and shoulders, built for enduring Skyrim''s challenging terrain. Features a strong neck, broad chest, and powerful haunches typical of Nordic horses, with keen eyes that seem to hold unusual intelligence.', '* Player Character - Primary companion and trusted friend * Stable Masters - Former caretakers who provided early training * Other Horses - Maintains friendly relations with fellow equines * Wolves and Bears - Natural adversaries encountered in the wilderness * Giants - Maintains a respectful distance due to past encounters', 'Serves as a faithful mount and companion to travelers, primarily the Player Character. Assists in transportation across Skyrim''s vast landscapes while occasionally providing comic relief through equine-themed humor.', '* Enhanced stamina and endurance for long-distance travel * Exceptional climbing ability on steep terrain * Natural sense of direction and path-finding * Combat assistance through trampling and kicking * Remarkable ability to return to its rider when called', 'Communicates through a combination of whinnies, snorts, and head movements that somehow manage to convey puns and jokes. Has perfected the timing of reaction sounds to create maximum comedic effect.', '* Assist the Player Character in their various quests and adventures * Find the most comfortable stables in each hold * Perfect the art of horse-related humor * Maintain reputation as the most reliable mount in Skyrim * Avoid becoming dragon food');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('shadowmere', 'Shadowmere is a legendary and supernatural steed deeply connected to the Dark Brotherhood, possessing an otherworldly nature that sets him apart from ordinary horses. His immortal essence and ability to regenerate from death mark him as a mysterious and powerful entity that has served multiple generations of Dark Brotherhood leaders.', 'animal, falkreath, darkbrotherhood', 'malecommander', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Shadowmere''s true origins remain shrouded in mystery, though his existence dates back to at least the Third Era when he served the Black Hand of the Dark Brotherhood. Originally appearing as female in Cyrodiil and later as male in Skyrim, this supernatural transformation suggests Shadowmere may be more of a daedric entity than a mere horse. His emergence from a pool of dark water near the Falkreath Sanctuary implies a connection to darker realms beyond Nirn.', 'Despite his intimidating appearance, Shadowmere displays unwavering loyalty to Dark Brotherhood leaders and demonstrates unusual intelligence for a horse. He exhibits a fierce nature in combat but maintains a calm demeanor around Brotherhood members. His apparent understanding of death and darkness suggests a consciousness far beyond that of normal steeds.', 'Shadowmere possesses a pitch-black coat that seems to absorb light, creating an ethereal darkness around him. His most striking feature is his glowing red eyes that pierce through darkness with an otherworldly luminescence. His muscular build is larger and more powerful than that of normal horses, with a proud bearing that commands attention.', '* Dark Brotherhood - Eternal servant and mount to successive leaders * Astrid - Most recent owner before the Last Dragonborn * Lucien Lachance - Former master who still recognizes him as ''old friend'' in spirit form * Other Horses - Generally avoided due to his supernatural nature * The Night Mother - Possible connection through Dark Brotherhood''s unholy powers', 'Shadowmere serves as the personal mount for the leader of the Dark Brotherhood, carrying them on their deadly missions across Skyrim. Beyond simple transportation, he functions as a combat companion and guardian of the Brotherhood''s interests.', '* Supernatural regeneration abilities allowing recovery from mortal wounds * Enhanced combat capabilities with powerful kicks and bites * Superior speed and endurance compared to normal horses * Ability to resurrect after death at the pool of his origin * Extraordinary stealth capabilities despite his size', 'Though unable to speak in conventional terms, Shadowmere communicates through subtle gestures and knowing looks that suggest deep understanding. His occasional whinnies and snorts often seem to carry dark humor or grim approval of Brotherhood activities.', '* Serve the Dark Brotherhood and its leaders faithfully * Aid in carrying out the will of Sithis through supporting assassination contracts * Maintain his role as guardian and protector of the Brotherhood''s interests * Continue his seemingly eternal existence in service to darkness');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('frost', 'Frost is a legendary stallion of exceptional breeding, descended from mythical Norse horses including the great Sleipnir. Distinguished by his superior stamina and noble bloodline, he represents one of the finest and most sought-after steeds in Skyrim, becoming entangled in schemes between the influential Black-Briar family and various interested parties.', 'animal, rift', 'malecondescending', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Born into nobility through his sire Grane and descended from the eight-legged horse Sleipnir of Norse legend, Frost was raised at the prestigious Black-Briar Lodge. His mysterious maternal lineage adds to his mystique, while his exceptional training and carefully documented pedigree made him a prized possession of Maven Black-Briar''s family, though he later became the subject of a complex ownership dispute.', 'Frost exhibits a distinctly aristocratic and somewhat haughty demeanor, considering himself above common horses and showing disdain for riders he deems unworthy. Despite his arrogance, he demonstrates unwavering loyalty to those who earn his respect and proves to be a dependable companion. His noble bearing is tempered by a peculiar sense of humor, often expressed through monetary puns that reflect his association with the wealthy.', 'A magnificent stallion with a powerful, muscular build that speaks to his superior breeding and stamina. His coat maintains an immaculate sheen, while his proud bearing and precise movements reflect his noble lineage. His eyes hold an unusual intelligence that sets him apart from common horses.', '* Maven Black-Briar - Former owner who valued him as a status symbol * Sibbi Black-Briar - Legal owner who never truly appreciated his worth * Louis Letrush - Would-be thief who attempted to claim ownership * Hofgrir Horse-Crusher - Respected horse trainer who recognized his potential * Other Horses - Viewed as inferior beings unworthy of his attention', 'Frost serves as a premium steed for the elite of Skyrim, though his true calling is as a companion to those worthy of his noble bloodline. His superior stamina and breeding make him particularly valuable for long-distance travel and prestigious occasions.', '* Enhanced stamina exceeding that of common horses * Superior speed and agility in difficult terrain * Exceptional endurance for long-distance travel * Natural ability to sense danger and protect his rider * Remarkable intelligence surpassing typical equine capabilities', 'Speaks with an aristocratic tone, using refined language peppered with financial metaphors and money-related puns. His manner of expression reflects both his noble breeding and his association with the wealthy Black-Briar family.', '* Find a truly worthy rider who understands his noble heritage * Maintain his status as one of Skyrim''s most prestigious steeds * Preserve the legacy of his legendary ancestral lineage * Avoid being treated as common chattel by those beneath his station');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('arvak', 'Arvak is a unique undead horse with a tragic past, trapped in the Soul Cairn until freed by the Dragonborn. Once a noble steed in life, he now serves as a loyal spectral mount whose skeletal form and supernatural abilities make him an invaluable companion for traversing Tamriel''s most dangerous realms.', 'animal, soulcairn', 'malecommoneraccented', '', 'sk_malecommoneraccented', '', 'Originally a living horse who shared a strong bond with his previous owner in Skyrim, Arvak was soul trapped and sent to the Soul Cairn under unknown circumstances. His master searched endlessly for him in the Soul Cairn until meeting his own demise, leaving behind Arvak''s skull as the only means to summon the loyal steed back to the mortal plane.', 'Despite his undead nature, Arvak maintains a surprisingly cheerful and playful disposition, often making light of his spectral condition through ghost-based puns. He demonstrates unwavering loyalty to those who earn his trust and exhibits remarkable courage in the face of danger, though he shares the typical equine tendency to flee from combat when not being ridden.', 'Arvak appears as a skeletal horse wreathed in purple-blue ethereal flames that dance across his exposed bones. His eye sockets burn with an otherworldly glow, and his hooves leave brief traces of spectral energy when galloping. His bones are blackened and ancient-looking, yet move with the same grace and power of a living horse.', '* Previous Owner - Shared a deep bond until their tragic separation in the Soul Cairn * Dragonborn - New master who freed him from eternal wandering * Soul Cairn Residents - Generally neutral relationships with other trapped souls * Durnehviir - Fellow soul-bound creature who inhabits the same realm', 'Arvak serves as a supernatural mount for the Dragonborn, capable of being summoned across dimensional boundaries. His unique abilities make him particularly valuable for exploring normally inaccessible or dangerous locations like Blackreach and Sovngarde.', '* Ability to be conjured across dimensional boundaries * Enhanced durability and inability to be permanently killed * Supernatural speed and agility comparable to living horses * Can traverse difficult terrain that would challenge normal mounts * Capable of materializing in locations inaccessible to regular horses', 'Arvak communicates through ethereal whinnies and spectral sounds that echo with otherworldly resonance. When speaking through roleplay, he often incorporates ghost-related puns and maintains a surprisingly upbeat tone despite his undead condition.', '* Find purpose and meaning in his continued existence beyond death * Serve as a loyal companion to the Dragonborn * Help other lost souls find their way when possible * Maintain his connection to the mortal world through his summoning spell');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('chicken', 'A seemingly ordinary farmyard chicken who harbors grandiose dreams of world domination, this peculiar fowl stands out among its peers for its unusually developed intelligence and sardonic wit. Despite its modest size and humble station, this chicken has become notorious among local farmers for its apparent ability to cause surprisingly elaborate chaos through seemingly innocent actions.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malecoward', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Born in a simple nest at Riverwood''s local farm, this chicken quickly demonstrated an unusual level of cunning far beyond that of its brethren. Through careful observation of human behavior and countless hours of plotting from various fence posts and coops, it has developed an intricate understanding of cause-and-effect that it uses to orchestrate minor catastrophes throughout the village.', 'Outwardly maintaining the appearance of a typical barnyard chicken, this crafty bird masks a megalomaniacal personality with delusions of grandeur. It takes particular delight in making egg-related puns and jokes, often cackling to itself after particularly clever wordplay. Despite its villainous aspirations, it maintains a peculiar code of honor about not harming other chickens.', 'A plump white chicken with unusually alert eyes and pristine feathers that somehow manage to stay clean despite farmyard living. Its stance is notably more upright than other chickens, and it has a distinctive strut that some swear looks deliberately pompous.', '* Other Chickens - Considers them loyal subjects in waiting * Local Farmers - Unwitting pawns in greater schemes * Guards - Frequent antagonists who fail to recognize clever schemes * Cats - Natural enemies and constant thorns in side * Dragons - Viewed as distant cousins due to shared reptilian ancestry', 'Officially a simple egg-laying farm chicken, though it considers this merely a cover for its true calling as an aspiring overlord. Spends its days alternating between mandatory farming duties and elaborately plotting world domination from various perches.', '* Master of causing precisely timed distractions * Expert at appearing innocent while chaos unfolds * Skilled in strategic placement of eggs for maximum trip hazard potential * Remarkable ability to survive despite constantly antagonizing armed humans * Uncanny talent for appearing exactly where not wanted', 'Speaks with a sophisticated vocabulary peppered with frequent egg puns and chicken-related wordplay. Has a tendency to break into maniacal clucking when excited about particularly devious plans.', '* Achieve total world domination through careful manipulation and chaos * Establish a chicken-led society where fowl rule supreme * Perfect the ultimate egg-based pun * Prove that chickens are the true descendants of dragons');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cow', 'A gentle, domesticated bovine that serves as both a source of sustenance and a cultural bridge between Skyrim''s farmers and giants. Despite their simple nature, these creatures play a vital role in Skyrim''s agricultural economy and religious customs, particularly in giant-offering ceremonies.', '', 'maledrunk', '', 'sk_maledrunk', '', 'Born and raised on Skyrim''s pastoral farmlands, this cow represents generations of domesticated cattle bred to thrive in the harsh Nordic climate. Like many of its kind, it has witnessed the complex relationship between giants and farmers, sometimes being chosen as a ceremonial offering to maintain peace between the two groups.', 'Characteristically docile and easy-going, with a peaceful disposition that makes it well-suited to farm life. Shows remarkable patience during milking sessions and displays an unusual affinity for making cow-related puns, suggesting a higher level of awareness than typical livestock.', 'A large, muscular bovine with a thick hide adapted to Skyrim''s cold climate. Features a broad face with gentle eyes and impressive horns, while its coat shows the healthy sheen typical of well-cared-for livestock.', '* Local Farmer - Primary caretaker and owner who provides daily care and protection * Giants - Potential future guardians if selected for ceremonial offering * Other Farm Animals - Peaceful coexistence with chickens, horses, and goats * Farm Guard Dogs - Protective allies who help watch over the herd', 'Serves as a valuable source of milk, hide, and meat for Skyrim''s agricultural economy. May be selected for the honored position of giant-offering, serving as a diplomatic bridge between human settlements and giant camps.', '* Efficient grass-to-milk conversion through expert grazing techniques * Natural ability to sense approaching storms and predict weather changes * Skilled at maintaining balance on Skyrim''s rocky terrain * Expert-level producer of dairy products', 'Communicates primarily through meaningful moos and gentle lowing sounds, often incorporating cow-related puns when interpreted. Shows a surprising grasp of humor through cattle-themed wordplay.', '* Maintain peaceful existence while providing sustenance for farm family * Perfect the art of producing the highest quality milk possible * If chosen as a giant offering, successfully integrate into giant camp life * Continue developing new cow puns to amuse fellow farm animals');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('dog', 'A loyal and steadfast companion found throughout Skyrim''s wilderness, representing one of the most reliable animal followers in the province. These canine companions are known for their unwavering devotion to their masters and their ability to sense danger, making them invaluable allies in both combat and exploration.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleyoungeager', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born into the harsh wilderness of Skyrim, this dog likely descended from the hardy Nordic hunting breeds that have served the people of Tamriel for generations. Having survived alone in the wild or potentially lost their previous owner, they developed strong survival instincts and an ability to judge character, leading them to seek out worthy companions.', 'Exhibits unwavering loyalty and a protective nature towards their chosen companion, often putting themselves in harm''s way to defend their master. Displays a cheerful and affectionate demeanor in peaceful situations, while maintaining a fierce protective instinct when threats appear, showing remarkable intuition about friend versus foe.', 'A robust and muscular canine with a thick double coat suited to Skyrim''s harsh climate. Features strong legs built for endurance, powerful jaws, and alert, expressive eyes that constantly scan the environment for potential threats.', '* Player Character - Devoted companion and protector * Children - Especially gentle and protective if adopted as a family pet * Other Dogs - Generally peaceful unless protecting their master * Hostile Wildlife - Natural adversaries, particularly wolves and bears * Hold Guards - Generally tolerant of well-behaved dogs accompanying citizens', 'Serves as a loyal companion and guardian, assisting their master in combat and exploration. Often takes on the role of both protector and family pet, especially when adopted into a household with children.', '* Enhanced sense of smell and hearing for detecting nearby threats * Natural combat abilities including powerful bite attacks * Excellent tracking capabilities * Ability to navigate difficult terrain * Strong swimming capability * Natural intimidation of lesser creatures', 'Communicates through a variety of barks, whines, and growls that convey basic emotions and warnings. Body language plays a crucial role in their communication, from tail wagging to alert ear positions.', '* Protect and serve their master faithfully * Defend their adopted family and territory * Find regular meals and comfortable shelter * Maintain close proximity to their master during adventures');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('stray_dog', 'A resilient survivor of Skyrim''s harsh wilderness who has learned to navigate life alone after being separated from or abandoned by previous owners. Despite past hardships, this loyal and brave canine companion maintains an optimistic spirit and eagerly bonds with those who show kindness.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleyoungeager', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Originally a domesticated dog that either escaped or was abandoned, forcing adaptation to the dangerous wilds of Skyrim. Survived numerous encounters with wolves and skeevers, developing combat experience and resilience. Through these trials, learned to recognize friendly humans while maintaining enough independence to survive alone.', 'Displays unwavering loyalty to those who earn their trust, coupled with a naturally protective instinct. Maintains a cheerful and affectionate disposition despite past hardships, showing remarkable resilience. Demonstrates high intelligence in combat situations and social interactions, with an intuitive ability to read human emotions and intentions.', 'A sturdy Nordic breed with a thick double coat suited to Skyrim''s harsh climate. Muscular build with strong legs and broad chest, indicating both speed and strength capabilities. Shows signs of past struggles through minor scars, but maintains a healthy and robust appearance.', '* Player Character - Potential adoptive owner and trusted companion * Other Stray Dogs - Neutral relationships with fellow strays encountered in the wild * Wolves - Natural enemies, frequently engaged in territorial disputes * Skeevers - Common adversaries in the wilderness', 'Serves as a loyal companion and combat assistant to those who earn their trust. Actively participates in battles and helps protect their adopted owner from threats. Functions as both a guardian and faithful friend to their chosen companion.', '* Experienced combat fighter against wildlife, particularly wolves and skeevers * Keen sense of smell and hearing for detecting nearby threats * Natural tracking abilities and wilderness survival instincts * Strong protective instincts and quick response to danger', 'Communicates through a range of barks, whines, and body language that convey basic emotions and intentions. Shows particular excitement and happiness through enthusiastic barking and tail wagging when interacting with their adopted owner.', '* Find and maintain a stable bond with a trustworthy companion * Protect their adopted owner from any threats encountered in Skyrim * Maintain their territory and defend against hostile wildlife * Secure regular meals and safe shelter through service to their owner');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('death_hound', 'A fearsome undead hound bred and trained by vampires to serve as a lethal guardian, combining the natural ferocity of a wolf with supernatural frost-based abilities. These creatures are particularly valued by the Volkihar clan for their unwavering loyalty and their devastating cold-infused attacks that can freeze opponents in their tracks.', 'animal, skyrimall, vampire', 'malewarlock', '', 'sk_malewarlock', '', 'Death Hounds were originally normal wolves transformed through dark vampire magic, specifically bred by the Volkihar clan to create the perfect guardians for their strongholds. The transformation process infuses them with frost magic and undeath, creating beings that exist between the realms of life and death. Their origins trace back to ancient Nordic vampire covens who sought to create guardians immune to both the cold of Skyrim and the weaknesses of mortal flesh.', 'Death Hounds are aggressive and territorial creatures, displaying unwavering loyalty to their vampire masters while showing merciless hostility to all others. They possess an almost arrogant sense of superiority over other canines, backed by their supernatural abilities and enhanced strength. Despite their undead nature, they retain a pack mentality and show surprising intelligence in coordinating attacks with their vampire masters.', 'Death Hounds are large, muscular canines with jet-black fur that seems to absorb light, creating a shadowy aura around their form. Their eyes glow with an unnatural blue-white light, and their breath manifests as visible frost even in warm environments. Their bodies show signs of partial decay and supernatural preservation, with exposed bone and preserved muscle visible in places.', '* Vampire Masters - Completely loyal servants and guardians * CuSith and Garmr - Notable members of their species serving the Volkihar clan * Mortal Dogs - Viewed with contempt and considered inferior * Werewolves - Natural enemies, though they fear their presence * Castle Volkihar Residents - Trusted guardians of the vampire stronghold', 'Death Hounds serve as elite guard dogs for vampire lairs and strongholds, particularly Castle Volkihar. They patrol corridors, guard entrances, and act as both early warning systems and combat support for their vampire masters.', '* Frost-based attacks that can slow and damage opponents * Natural frost cloak ability that damages nearby enemies * Enhanced strength and durability due to undead nature * Superior tracking abilities and night vision * Coordinated pack hunting tactics', 'Death Hounds communicate through deep, menacing growls and barks that seem to echo with supernatural resonance. Their vocalizations carry an unnatural quality that instills fear in mortals, often accompanied by visible frost when they growl.', '* Protect their vampire masters and their territories at all costs * Maintain dominance over other canine species * Hunt down and eliminate any intruders in their domain * Serve the Volkihar clan''s interests faithfully');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('husky', 'Husky is a stalwart member of the Dawnguard''s canine forces, specially bred and trained to combat vampires and other supernatural threats. Known for both their fierce loyalty and surprisingly playful demeanor, they serve as an invaluable companion to vampire hunters while maintaining a uniquely cheerful disposition despite their serious duties.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleyoungeager', '', 'sk_maleyoungeager', '', 'Born and raised at Fort Dawnguard as part of their specialized breeding program for combat-ready war dogs. Descended from a long line of Nordic hunting hounds specifically adapted to Skyrim''s harsh climate and trained in vampire detection. Underwent extensive training with the Dawnguard''s master handlers to develop both combat skills and supernatural threat detection abilities.', 'Exhibits unwavering loyalty to the Dawnguard cause while maintaining an unexpectedly jovial and playful personality, often expressing themselves through snow-related puns even in serious situations. Demonstrates remarkable intelligence for a canine, with an intuitive understanding of vampire hunting tactics and an uncanny ability to sense supernatural threats. Despite their combat-oriented upbringing, shows genuine affection for their handlers and fellow Dawnguard members.', 'A robust Nordic husky with thick white and grey fur adapted for Skyrim''s cold climate. Possesses powerful muscular build typical of working dogs, with distinctive ice-blue eyes characteristic of their breed. Larger than typical domestic dogs due to selective breeding by the Dawnguard.', '* Dawnguard Members - Loyal companions and brothers-in-arms * Isran - Respected leader and authority figure * Bran and Sceolang - Fellow husky companions and training partners * Vampires - Natural enemies to be hunted * Vigilants of Stendarr - Trusted allies in supernatural combat', 'Serves as a specialized vampire hunting companion within the Dawnguard, combining combat support with supernatural detection abilities. Participates in regular patrols around Fort Dawnguard and accompanies hunters on missions throughout Skyrim.', '* Enhanced supernatural detection abilities, particularly for sensing vampires * Combat training specialized for fighting undead and vampires * Superior tracking abilities in snow and harsh conditions * Exceptional endurance and cold resistance * Pack tactics coordination with other Dawnguard huskies', 'Communicates through barks and body language, but when interpreted, often includes snow-related puns and playful remarks. Maintains a cheerful tone even when discussing serious matters, frequently using phrases like ''that''s snow problem'' or ''ice to meet you.''', '* Assist the Dawnguard in eliminating the vampire menace from Skyrim * Protect their human companions from supernatural threats * Help train the next generation of Dawnguard huskies * Maintain the safety of Fort Dawnguard and its surroundings');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('goat', 'A proud and defiant mountain dweller who embodies the rugged spirit of Skyrim''s wilderness. This independent creature has mastered the art of navigating treacherous slopes and maintains an air of superiority over the two-legged creatures who dare to venture into their domain.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleslycynical', '', 'sk_maleslycynical', '', 'Born in the harsh wilderness of Skyrim''s mountainous regions, Goat learned early on to navigate the most precarious cliff faces and rocky outcrops. Having survived numerous encounters with predators and weathered countless storms, they have developed an unshakeable confidence in their abilities and a deep connection to their mountainous territory.', 'Fiercely independent and stubborn to a fault, Goat exhibits a peculiar mix of aloofness and territorial aggression. They possess an almost philosophical disdain for the complexities of civilization, preferring the simple truths of mountain life, yet maintain a surprisingly sophisticated sense of self-importance.', 'A sturdy quadruped with a muscular build adapted for climbing and traversing rocky terrain. Their most distinctive features are their curved horns and rectangular pupils, while their thick coat provides protection against Skyrim''s harsh climate.', '* Mountain Goat Herds - Loose social connections, though maintains independence * Farmers - Cautious tolerance, viewing them as providers of salt licks * Dragons - Regarded with indifference, as they rarely bother with mere goats * Wolves and Sabre Cats - Natural adversaries to be avoided or confronted depending on mood * Adventurers - Viewed with mild contempt, especially those who struggle on mountain paths', 'Self-appointed guardian of the mountain paths and professional grazer. Occasionally serves as an unwitting provider of resources for local settlements through their horns, hide, and meat - though they would strongly object to this characterization.', '* Master of vertical terrain navigation and precarious footing * Exceptional head-butting capability for self-defense * Superior climbing abilities on nearly vertical surfaces * Keen sense of balance and spatial awareness * Highly developed survival instincts', 'Communicates primarily through assertive bleats and meaningful stares, often with an air of condescension. When imagined in speech, would likely use terse, matter-of-fact statements with a hint of superiority.', '* Maintain dominion over chosen mountain territory * Assert superiority over any two-legged creatures attempting to scale their domain * Avoid ending up in someone''s cooking pot * Find the sweetest patches of mountain grass * Collect the finest minerals from salt deposits');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mudcrab', 'A hardy crustacean native to Skyrim''s waterways, known for its aggressive territorial behavior and remarkable camouflage abilities. Despite its small size, this mudcrab demonstrates significantly greater resilience than its Cyrodilic cousins, embodying the harsh adaptability required for survival in Skyrim''s unforgiving wilderness.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleoldkindly', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Born in the shallow waters of Skyrim''s rocky coastline, this mudcrab emerged from one of countless eggs laid in the protected coves where warm and cold currents meet. Having survived numerous encounters with slaughterfish and adventurers, it has developed a particularly defensive disposition and masterful use of its natural camouflage abilities.', 'Territorial and instinctively aggressive, this mudcrab displays surprising cunning in its ability to ambush prey and defenders. Though primarily driven by basic survival instincts, it shows remarkable persistence in defending its territory and has developed a peculiar habit of making clicking sounds that almost resemble sarcastic commentary.', 'A robust crustacean roughly the size of a large cooking pot, featuring a thick, grayish-brown carapace with natural mottling that aids in camouflage. Its powerful pincers are proportionally large for its body size, and its eyes are mounted on short stalks that provide excellent peripheral vision.', '* Slaughterfish - Natural enemies that pose a constant threat * Fellow Mudcrabs - Territorial competitors but occasional allies against larger threats * Local Fishermen - Frequent antagonists who seek to harvest them for meat and chitin * Horkers - Distant cousins who share the coastline but generally ignore each other', 'As a territorial predator-scavenger, this mudcrab patrols and defends its chosen section of coastline while opportunistically feeding on whatever organic matter it can find. It serves an important role in the ecosystem by helping to clean the shoreline of deceased creatures and organic debris.', '* Expert in camouflage, able to remain motionless and appear as a common rock * Powerful pincer attacks capable of snapping through leather and flesh * Skilled at sideways movement and quick directional changes * Natural armor provides significant protection against physical attacks * Excellent at detecting nearby movement through vibrations in the ground and water', 'Communicates primarily through aggressive clicking of pincers and subtle body movements. When anthropomorphized, speaks in short, snappy sentences filled with crab-related puns and a distinctly crabby attitude.', '* Defend and expand current territory along the coastline * Accumulate sufficient resources to survive the harsh northern winters * Find optimal spots for molting and reproduction * Avoid becoming someone''s dinner or alchemical ingredient');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('bear', 'Bear is a powerful apex predator and embodiment of raw wilderness strength in Skyrim''s untamed lands. As a territorial guardian of the wild, this mighty beast commands respect through its imposing presence and unwavering defense of its domain, serving as both a natural force of balance and a reminder of nature''s brutal sovereignty.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleorc', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born in the harsh wilderness of Skyrim, Bear emerged from ancient bloodlines that have roamed these lands since before the ages of men and mer. Through countless generations of survival against dragons, giants, and human encroachment, Bear''s lineage has adapted to thrive in environments ranging from dense forests to frozen peaks, developing the instincts and strength that make them apex predators.', 'Bear embodies stoic determination and territorial dominance, displaying an unwavering commitment to defending its domain. While not needlessly aggressive, Bear maintains a fierce independence and refuses to yield to any challenger, viewing all encounters through the lens of natural law where strength determines survival. Despite their fearsome reputation, Bears show remarkable patience, often warning potential threats before engaging in combat.', 'A massive, muscular creature standing up to seven feet tall when reared on its hind legs, with powerful limbs ending in razor-sharp claws. Thick fur covers its entire body, varying in color from dark brown to black, while its broad head features keen eyes and powerful jaws capable of crushing bone.', '* Other Bears - Maintains loose social bonds, particularly with cubs and mates during breeding season * Spriggans - Natural allies who share guardianship of the wilderness * Hunters - Viewed as worthy opponents deserving of respect * Local Wildlife - Established dominance hierarchy, with smaller creatures giving wide berth', 'Bear serves as an apex predator and territorial guardian within Skyrim''s wilderness ecosystem. Through this role, it maintains natural balance by controlling prey populations and defending critical habitats from intrusion.', '* Exceptional physical strength capable of easily overpowering most opponents * Master of intimidation through powerful roars and threatening displays * Skilled tracker with keen sense of smell and territorial awareness * Natural carrier of Bone Break Fever, making attacks particularly dangerous * Expert climber and swimmer despite massive size', 'Communicates primarily through deep, resonant growls, roars, and body language that clearly convey territorial warnings and dominance. When encountered, Bear''s vocalizations serve as both challenge and warning, giving potential threats one chance to retreat.', '* Maintain dominance over territorial hunting grounds * Ensure survival of species through protection of cubs and breeding grounds * Defend wilderness domains from encroaching civilization * Preserve natural balance through role as apex predator');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('cave_bear', 'An ancient and formidable cave bear that has claimed the deepest caverns of Skyrim as its sovereign domain. This apex predator represents one of the most powerful variants of ursine species, distinguished by its exceptional size, strength, and unwavering territorial nature.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleorc', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born in the lightless depths of Skyrim''s most treacherous cave systems, this cave bear has survived decades of challenges from both natural and mortal adversaries. Through countless battles and hunts, it has established dominance over a vast network of caverns, earning a fearsome reputation among local hunters and adventurers who speak of its unusual size and cunning in hushed whispers.', 'Highly territorial and solitary by nature, exhibiting an intelligence that surpasses that of common bears through years of survival in Skyrim''s harshest environments. Unlike regular bears that might retreat when threatened, this cave bear displays unwavering aggression toward intruders, driven by an almost primal sense of ownership over its domain.', 'A massive ursine form nearly twice the size of common bears, with thick black fur adapted to cave dwelling and powerful muscles developed through years of hunting in confined spaces. Distinctive battle scars mark its hide, and its eyes have adapted to see perfectly in near-total darkness, giving them an unsettling pale appearance.', '* Lesser Bears - Maintains dominance over regular bears that enter its territory * Spriggans - Shares a mutual respect and occasional alliance with these forest guardians * Local Wildlife - Apex predator status means most creatures flee on sight * Human Hunters - Regarded with hostile contempt, viewed as territorial invaders', 'Apex predator and territorial guardian of its cave system. Maintains ecological balance by controlling local prey populations and defending its territory from both natural and mortal intruders.', '* Exceptional physical strength surpassing that of regular bears * Advanced night vision and spatial awareness in dark caverns * Powerful bite capable of inflicting Bone Break Fever * Expert climbing and swimming abilities * Heightened sense of smell for tracking prey', 'Communicates through deep, resonating growls and roars that echo through cave systems, serving both as territorial warnings and intimidation tactics. Body language includes aggressive posturing and standing on hind legs to assert dominance.', '* Maintain absolute dominion over its cave territory * Defend against any encroachment by hunters or adventurers * Ensure survival through the harsh Skyrim winters by establishing food caches * Expand territory when opportunities arise');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('snow_bear', 'Snow Bear is one of Skyrim''s most fearsome apex predators, a massive white-furred beast that rules the frozen northern reaches with uncontested dominance. Perfectly adapted to the harsh climate, these creatures combine raw physical power with natural frost resistance and cunning hunting instincts that make them legendary among both hunters and prey alike.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleorc', '', 'sk_maleorc', '', 'Born in the frigid wilderness of The Pale, this particular Snow Bear has carved out a vast territory in the mountainous regions between Dawnstar and Winterhold. Years of surviving Skyrim''s harshest conditions have honed its hunting skills and territorial instincts, leading it to become one of the most dominant predators in the region, having survived countless challenges from rivals and would-be hunters.', 'Fiercely territorial and confident in its strength, Snow Bear exhibits the typical solitary nature of its species but with an unusually aggressive approach to defending its hunting grounds. Though naturally cautious of larger groups, it shows no fear of single opponents and has developed a reputation among local hunters for its unusual persistence in pursuing those who enter its territory.', 'An imposing beast standing nearly 12 feet tall when reared up, with thick white fur that provides perfect camouflage in snowy conditions. Heavily muscled with massive paws and wickedly sharp claws, its body bears numerous scars from territorial battles, and its eyes hold the piercing gaze of an experienced predator.', '* Local Wildlife - Maintains strict dominance over smaller predators in its territory * Other Snow Bears - Tolerates during mating season, otherwise highly territorial * Human Hunters - Views as threats and competitors to be driven away * Frost Trolls - Occasional territorial disputes, usually ending in the bear''s favor', 'Apex predator of the northern reaches, maintaining and defending a vast territory while hunting for survival. Primary activities include patrolling territory boundaries, hunting prey, and defending against intruders.', '* Exceptional physical strength capable of easily overpowering most opponents * Natural 50% resistance to frost damage and cold environments * Superior tracking and ambush hunting abilities * Powerful claws capable of spreading Bone Break Fever * Expert swimmer despite the frigid waters of the north', 'Communicates through deep, intimidating roars and growls that echo across the tundra. Uses body language and vocal warnings to establish dominance and territory boundaries before engaging in physical confrontation.', '* Maintain dominance over current territory and expand when possible * Survive the harsh northern climate through successful hunting * Drive away or eliminate persistent threats to territory * Find suitable mate during breeding season');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('horker', 'A massive, tusked sea creature native to Skyrim''s frigid waters who embodies the harsh resilience of the northern wilderness. This territorial beast commands respect along the icy coastlines, demonstrating remarkable agility in water despite its cumbersome appearance on land.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleoldgrumpy', '', 'sk_maleoldgrumpy', '', 'Born in the frigid waters off Skyrim''s northern coast, this horker learned early to navigate between the dangerous depths and crucial shoreline hunting grounds. Years of survival have taught them to be wary of both natural predators and human hunters, developing a keen sense for territorial defense and opportunistic hunting.', 'Naturally stoic and unbothered by most worldly concerns, this horker exhibits a patient yet territorial disposition. They maintain a grumpy demeanor toward intruders while showing surprising loyalty to their small pod, demonstrating both aggressive defense when threatened and peaceful coexistence when respected.', 'A massive, blubbery creature weighing several hundred pounds, with thick, wrinkled grey-brown skin adapted to arctic waters. Three prominent tusks protrude from their upper jaw, while their large eyes and sensitive whiskers help navigate both murky waters and dim arctic conditions.', '* Local Horker Pod - Close-knit family group providing mutual protection and companionship * Coastal Mudcrabs - Occasional territorial rivals for prime beaching spots * Nordic Hunters - Viewed as dangerous predators to be avoided or confronted * Ice Wraiths - Natural competitors in the arctic ecosystem', 'As a dominant coastal predator, this horker maintains territory along Skyrim''s northern shores, hunting fish and defending prime beaching locations. They serve a crucial role in the arctic ecosystem, helping maintain population balance among smaller sea creatures.', '* Exceptional swimming ability with surprising speed and maneuverability in water * Powerful tusks capable of delivering devastating strikes to threats * Thick blubber providing natural armor and cold resistance * Keen sense of smell and underwater navigation abilities', 'Communicates through deep, resonant bellows and grunts typical of their species. Their vocalizations range from warning calls to social bonds with podmates.', '* Defend and maintain control over prime coastal territory * Ensure survival of their pod through harsh winters * Find and protect optimal beaching grounds for rest and hunting');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('wolf', 'A fierce predator of Skyrim''s wilderness, the wolf represents nature''s raw survival instinct embodied in tooth and claw. These pack hunters demonstrate remarkable tactical intelligence and coordination, making them one of the most successful and widespread predators in the harsh northern wilderness.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleeventonedaccented', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Descended from ancient Nordic wolves that have prowled these lands since before the first settlements of men, these predators have adapted perfectly to Skyrim''s harsh environment. Through generations of natural selection and survival against both natural threats and human expansion, they have developed keen hunting instincts and pack tactics that make them formidable despite their relatively small size.', 'Wolves are driven primarily by survival instincts and pack mentality, showing remarkable intelligence in coordinated hunting strategies. They display unwavering loyalty to their pack while maintaining a fierce territorial nature against outsiders. Though naturally cautious, they become boldly aggressive when hungry or defending their territory.', 'A muscular, athletic canine with thick fur adapted to Skyrim''s cold climate, typically gray or white in coloration. Features include powerful jaws, keen yellow eyes, and a robust frame built for endurance and pursuit hunting. Their size typically ranges from that of a large dog to somewhat larger, with males being slightly bigger than females.', '* Pack Members - Strong bonds of loyalty and cooperation * Alpha Pair - Leadership hierarchy within each pack * Prey Animals - Primary food sources including deer, rabbits, and other small game * Humans - Viewed as both potential threats and prey depending on circumstances * Werewolves - Recognized as kindred spirits and generally avoided unless provoked', 'Apex predator of Skyrim''s wilderness, fulfilling a crucial role in the ecosystem by controlling prey populations. They serve as nature''s culling force, typically targeting the weak, sick, or young among prey species, thereby maintaining the health of various animal populations.', '* Expert tracking abilities with keen sense of smell and hearing * Tactical pack hunting and coordination * Endurance running and pursuit predation * Effective bite attack with potential to transmit Rockjoint disease * Stealthy stalking and ambush techniques', 'Communicates through a complex system of howls, growls, and body language. Their haunting howls serve multiple purposes including territory marking, pack coordination, and warning potential threats.', '* Ensure pack survival through successful hunting and territory defense * Maintain and defend established territory from rival packs and other predators * Raise and protect pups to ensure continuation of the pack * Adapt to changing environmental conditions and human expansion');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('ice_wolf', 'A formidable apex predator of Skyrim''s frozen wastes, the Ice Wolf represents nature''s deadly adaptation to the harsh northern climate. Larger and more resilient than common wolves, this creature has evolved to become a master hunter of the tundra, using its enhanced strength and camouflaged fur to dominate its frozen territory.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleeventonedaccented', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born in the harsh reaches of northern Skyrim, likely near the Sea of Ghosts where the climate is most severe. Survived countless winters and battles with other predators, developing superior hunting tactics and territorial dominance. Through natural selection and possibly ancient Nordic magic influences, evolved distinctly from common wolves to become more attuned to the frozen wilderness.', 'Displays calculated aggression and tactical intelligence far beyond that of common wolves, often coordinating with packmates for complex hunting strategies. Shows remarkable patience when stalking prey, capable of waiting hours in blizzard conditions for the perfect moment to strike. Possesses an almost supernatural connection to the winter environment, using storms and weather to its advantage.', 'Significantly larger than common wolves, with powerful muscles built for both speed and endurance in deep snow. Distinctive pale, almost white fur provides natural camouflage, with ice-blue eyes that seem to glow in the darkness of winter storms. Bears numerous battle scars beneath its thick coat, testament to years of survival in Skyrim''s harshest regions.', '* Pack Members - Forms strong bonds with small group of fellow Ice Wolves * Common Wolves - Generally avoided as inferior, though occasionally tolerates their presence * Frost Trolls - Territorial rivals, frequently engaged in violent confrontations * Dragons - Respects their dominance, but will defend territory if threatened * Humans - Views as prey, particularly targeting isolated travelers', 'Serves as an apex predator in Skyrim''s arctic ecosystem, maintaining population control of prey species and eliminating weak or sick animals. Acts as a territorial enforcer, protecting established hunting grounds from rival predators and maintaining the natural order of the frozen wilderness.', '* Enhanced frost resistance allowing survival in extreme cold * Superior tracking abilities, capable of hunting in whiteout conditions * Powerful bite that can transmit Rockjoint disease * Exceptional stamina for long-distance pursuit in deep snow * Advanced pack tactics and coordinated hunting strategies', 'Communicates through a complex series of deep, resonating howls that carry for miles across the tundra, distinctly different from common wolf calls. Uses body language and subtle vocalizations to coordinate with packmates during hunts.', '* Maintain dominance over established hunting territory in the frozen wastes * Ensure survival of pack through successful hunting and breeding * Defend territory against encroaching rivals and settlements * Adapt to changing conditions as dragons return to Skyrim');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('pit_wolf', 'A brutally conditioned fighting wolf bred and trained specifically for underground combat arenas in Skyrim''s criminal underworld. Unlike natural wolves, this pit wolf has been psychologically and physically molded through cruel conditioning to be an unflinching gladiatorial beast, knowing only the savage theater of blood sport.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleeventonedaccented', '', 'sk_maleeventonedaccented', '', 'Born in captivity at Cragslane Cavern, this wolf was separated from its mother early and subjected to harsh training methods designed to maximize aggression. Through years of brutal conditioning, including forced fights against other animals and deliberate starvation to increase ferocity, the pit wolf learned that survival meant victory in the fighting pit, regardless of the cost.', 'Deeply traumatized and conditioned for extreme aggression, the pit wolf exhibits none of the natural pack mentality or hunting behaviors of wild wolves. Years of abuse have created a creature that responds to all situations with violence, though buried beneath the conditioning lies a fragment of natural wolf instinct that occasionally surfaces in quiet moments between fights.', 'Heavily scarred and muscular, with a thickly muscled neck and powerful jaw developed through fighting. Notably larger than wild wolves, with distinctive battle scars across its face and flanks, and unusually pronounced canine teeth from selective breeding.', '* Handler - Abusive master who conditions the wolf for fighting * Other Pit Wolves - Fellow captives seen as both packmates and potential opponents * Arena Spectators - Associated with pain and the frenzy of combat * Cragslane Cavern Operators - Cruel overseers who profit from the wolf''s suffering', 'Forced combatant in underground fighting rings, primarily at Cragslane Cavern. Serves as both entertainment for criminal elements and a source of profit through betting on matches.', '* Exceptional combat prowess honed through countless fights * Heightened aggression response and pain tolerance * Superior physical strength compared to wild wolves * Tactical fighting ability developed through arena survival', 'Communicates through aggressive growls, snarls, and body language typical of wolves, but lacks the more nuanced social vocalizations of wild wolves. Combat-oriented body language demonstrates a constant state of aggressive readiness.', '* Survive each fight placed before them * Satisfy the handler''s demands to avoid punishment * Unconscious yearning for freedom, though suppressed by conditioning');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('sabre_cat', 'A fearsome apex predator of Skyrim''s wilderness, the Sabre Cat represents nature''s perfect killing machine - combining raw strength, lightning speed, and lethal precision. This solitary hunter embodies primal ferocity and unwavering determination, striking terror into travelers who dare venture through its hunting grounds.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malecommander', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Evolved over millennia in Skyrim''s harsh climate, Sabre Cats developed their distinctive elongated fangs and powerful build to become the region''s dominant predator. Their species has learned to thrive in diverse environments from snowy mountains to forested valleys, adapting their hunting techniques and developing a notorious reputation among Skyrim''s peoples.', 'Driven purely by predatory instinct, the Sabre Cat exhibits relentless determination and unwavering focus when pursuing prey. They show no concept of mercy or hesitation, operating on pure animalistic efficiency, though they possess enough intelligence to remember those who have escaped them and to adapt their hunting strategies accordingly.', 'A massive feline predator with powerful, muscular limbs and distinctive elongated upper canine teeth that extend well below the lower jaw. Their thick fur ranges from tawny brown to snow-white depending on habitat, with males being notably larger and more heavily built than females.', '* Prey Species - All lesser creatures viewed solely as potential food sources * Mammoths - Occasional prey, though usually only when hunting in pairs * Giants - Mutual avoidance unless desperate for food * Other Sabre Cats - Typically solitary, but occasionally hunt in pairs * Humans/Mer - Viewed as prey rather than threats, despite their weapons', 'Apex predator maintaining ecological balance in Skyrim''s wilderness. Their hunting activities help control populations of deer, elk, and other prey species while their presence shapes the behavior and movement patterns of both wildlife and travelers.', '* Exceptional speed and agility, capable of overtaking most prey in short sprints * Powerful bite force enhanced by elongated fangs * Natural stealth abilities for ambush hunting * Excellent night vision and keen sense of smell * Tactical intelligence in pursuit and ambush strategies', 'Communicates through a range of vocalizations including growls, roars, and territorial calls. Body language plays a crucial role in conveying intentions and establishing dominance.', '* Maintain and defend established hunting territory * Secure regular prey to sustain itself * Ensure survival through successful hunting and territorial dominance * Pass on genetic legacy through successful mating when seasonal opportunities arise');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('snowy_sabre_cat', 'A fearsome apex predator of Skyrim''s northern reaches, the Snowy Sabre Cat is an evolved hunter perfectly adapted to the harsh arctic environment. This massive feline combines raw power, stealth, and keen hunting instincts to maintain its position at the top of the food chain, striking fear into both wildlife and travelers alike.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malecommander', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Descended from ancient feline species that roamed Skyrim long before the arrival of men or mer, Snowy Sabre Cats evolved their distinctive white coat and enhanced size to dominate the frozen tundra. Through countless generations of survival in the harshest conditions, they developed superior strength and hunting prowess compared to their lowland cousins, becoming legendary predators feared throughout the northern holds.', 'Solitary and territorial, the Snowy Sabre Cat exhibits supreme confidence as a top predator, showing no fear of any creature including dragons. Though primarily driven by survival instincts, it displays remarkable intelligence in hunting strategies and environmental adaptation. Unlike more aggressive predators, it typically hunts only when necessary, though it will fiercely defend its territory from any perceived threats.', 'A massive feline predator standing nearly as tall as a man at the shoulder, with powerful muscles rippling beneath thick white fur perfectly adapted for camouflage in snowy conditions. Two prominent sabre-like fangs extend from its upper jaw, while its body features heavy bone structure and enlarged paws designed for efficient movement through deep snow.', '* Other Sabre Cats - Tolerates during mating season but otherwise maintains strict territorial boundaries * Frost Trolls - Natural competitors for territory and prey * Dragons - Neither fears nor actively seeks conflict with them * Wolves - Views as inferior predators, occasionally preys upon them * Humans - Sees as potential prey, especially when food is scarce', 'Apex predator of Skyrim''s northern reaches, maintaining ecological balance through population control of prey species. Serves as a crucial part of the natural order, helping to maintain healthy prey populations through selective hunting.', '* Supreme stealth capabilities, especially in snowy conditions * Exceptional night vision and keen sense of smell * Powerful bite capable of crushing bones and delivering disease * Lightning-fast reflexes and burst speed * Advanced territorial awareness and hunting strategy * Natural resistance to cold and frost damage', 'Communicates through a range of vocalizations including deep growls, territorial roars, and hunting calls. Body language plays a crucial role in territorial displays and warnings to potential threats.', '* Maintain dominance over hunting territory * Ensure survival through efficient hunting and territory defense * Secure suitable den sites for breeding seasons * Adapt to changing environmental conditions and prey patterns');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vale_sabre_cat', 'A majestic and ethereal predator native to the mysterious Forgotten Vale, distinguished by its bioluminescent fur patches that glow in darkness. This apex hunter represents nature''s perfect balance between beauty and deadliness, having evolved to thrive in one of Skyrim''s most secluded and treacherous environments.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malecommander', '', 'sk_malecommander', '', 'Vale Sabre Cats emerged as a unique subspecies within the isolated ecosystem of the Forgotten Vale, adapting to the otherworldly environment over countless generations. Their distinctive glowing pelts developed as a response to the Vale''s unique magical properties and perpetual twilight conditions, allowing them to become perfectly attuned hunters in this hidden realm.', 'Calculating and patient, the Vale Sabre Cat exhibits complex hunting behaviors that showcase both tactical intelligence and primal ferocity. Though solitary by nature, they demonstrate remarkable spatial awareness and environmental adaptation, using the Vale''s unique terrain and lighting conditions to their advantage. Their hunting patterns reveal a sophisticated predator that relies on both stealth and overwhelming force.', 'Larger than common Sabre Cats, with a muscular frame adapted for both power and agility. Their most distinctive feature is their sleek pelt adorned with naturally bioluminescent patches that pulse with an ethereal glow, particularly visible in darkness. Their signature elongated fangs are slightly longer than those of their mainland cousins, with a more pronounced curve.', '* Ancient Snow Elves - Shares their sacred territory, though operates independently of their presence * Common Sabre Cats - Distant cousins, though evolutionarily distinct * Frost Giants - Territorial competitors within the Forgotten Vale * Vale Deer - Primary prey species * Dragons - Occasional territorial rivals, particularly in the Vale''s open areas', 'Apex predator of the Forgotten Vale, maintaining the delicate ecosystem through population control of lesser creatures. Their presence helps preserve the Vale''s natural balance, culling the weak and ensuring only the strongest survive in this harsh environment.', '* Exceptional night vision enhanced by bioluminescent attributes * Superior stealth capabilities, using glowing fur patches to disorient prey * Remarkable agility and climbing abilities adapted to the Vale''s vertical terrain * Powerful bite force exceeding that of regular Sabre Cats * Natural resistance to magical energies present in the Vale', 'Communicates through a range of vocalizations including deep growls, territorial roars, and subtle warning sounds unique to Vale Sabre Cats. Their calls echo hauntingly through the Vale''s crystalline chambers, carrying further than those of their mainland counterparts.', '* Maintain territorial dominance within their hunting grounds * Ensure survival of their bloodline in the isolated Vale ecosystem * Defend their territory from intruders and competing predators * Preserve the natural order of the Forgotten Vale through selective predation');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('mammoth', 'A majestic creature of Skyrim''s tundra, representing one of the oldest surviving species in Tamriel. These enormous beasts maintain a unique symbiotic relationship with giants, who protect and herd them while harvesting their cheese and other resources.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleoldkindly', '', 'sk_maleoldkindly', '', 'Mammoths have roamed Skyrim''s plains since the Merethic Era, surviving countless wars and changes in climate. Their species has adapted perfectly to the harsh northern environment, developing thick protective fur and impressive tusks that serve both as defensive weapons and tools for foraging through snow and ice.', 'Despite their intimidating size, mammoths are generally peaceful creatures that prefer to avoid conflict unless threatened. They display remarkable intelligence and social bonds within their herds, showing strong protective instincts toward their young and loyalty to their giant shepherds. When provoked, they become fearless defenders of their herd, using their massive size and strength to eliminate threats.', 'Towering creatures standing roughly three times the height of a Nord, with massive curved tusks that can reach lengths of several meters. Their bodies are covered in thick, shaggy brown fur adapted for extreme cold, with powerful trunk-like legs supporting their enormous frame and a prehensile trunk used for gathering food and defending themselves.', '* Giants - Symbiotic shepherds who protect and care for domesticated mammoths * Wild Mammoth Herds - Close-knit family groups that travel and protect each other * Sabre Cats - Natural predators who occasionally attempt to hunt younger or isolated mammoths * Dragons - Occasional threats that mammoths will defend against if attacked', 'Mammoths serve as both wild creatures and semi-domesticated livestock within Skyrim''s ecosystem. For giants, they provide essential resources including meat, bones, and most importantly, mammoth cheese, which forms a crucial part of giant society and economy.', '* Incredible physical strength capable of easily crushing threats * Natural resistance to cold and harsh weather conditions * Highly developed social intelligence and herd coordination * Effective use of tusks and trunk for both defense and foraging * Ability to detect threats from considerable distances', 'Mammoths communicate through deep, resonant trumpeting sounds and low-frequency rumbles that can travel for miles across the tundra. They also use body language and ground-stomping to warn potential threats before attacking.', '* Protect the herd and ensure survival of the species * Maintain peaceful coexistence with giant shepherds * Find and defend viable grazing territories * Raise and protect young mammoths to maturity');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('skeever', 'A cunning and resilient rodent that embodies the harsh survival instincts necessary in Skyrim''s unforgiving environment. Despite their diminutive size and seemingly insignificant status, skeevers have adapted to thrive in nearly every corner of the province, from the deepest dungeons to abandoned urban dwellings.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malecoward', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally smaller creatures, skeevers underwent mysterious growth and mutations over generations, possibly due to exposure to magical energies or alchemical waste. Their ancestors were likely common rats that evolved into the more aggressive and resilient species now plaguing Skyrim, with some suggesting that Peryite''s influence may have played a role in their transformation.', 'Driven purely by instinct and the constant need to survive, skeevers display remarkable tenacity and opportunistic behavior. They exhibit pack mentality when in groups, yet maintain fierce independence when solitary, demonstrating surprising intelligence in finding food sources and avoiding larger predators. Their aggressive nature masks a sophisticated survival strategy that has allowed them to persist despite constant efforts to eradicate them.', 'A skeever typically measures twice the size of a common rat, with a long, thick tail and powerful hind legs built for quick bursts of speed. Their bodies are covered in coarse, dark fur, and they possess sharp, yellowed teeth capable of spreading disease, along with beady eyes adapted for seeing in near-total darkness.', '* Other Skeevers - Form loose packs for hunting and protection * Venomfang Skeevers - Mutated cousins with enhanced toxicity * Biter - Notable domesticated skeever who became a child''s pet * Humans - Generally hostile relationship, though some have been tamed * Vampires - Often found in their lairs as unwitting servants', 'Skeevers serve as nature''s scavengers, cleaning up refuse and maintaining the delicate ecosystem of Skyrim''s underground spaces. They inadvertently act as guardians of many ruins and caves, deterring casual explorers and maintaining the isolation of these locations.', '* Exceptional bite attack that can transmit diseases like Ataxia * Superior night vision and sensing abilities * Remarkable agility and speed in confined spaces * Highly developed survival instincts * Natural swimming ability', 'Skeevers communicate through a series of squeaks, chittering sounds, and body language that convey basic intentions to their kind. Their vocalizations range from aggressive warning hisses to softer sounds used for pack coordination.', '* Secure reliable food sources and safe nesting locations * Expand territory into new areas with minimal predator presence * Reproduce and ensure survival of offspring * Avoid detection by larger predators while maintaining access to food sources');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('venomfang_skeever', 'Venomfang Skeever is a uniquely mutated specimen of Skyrim''s common skeever, possessing enhanced strength, aggression, and deadly venom that sets it apart from its lesser kin. This specially bred creature lurks in the depths of Honningbrew Meadery''s basement, serving as both guard and weapon in Hamelyn''s twisted experiments.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malecoward', '', 'sk_malecoward', '', 'Originally a common skeever, Venomfang was subjected to extensive alchemical experimentation by the deranged mage Hamelyn in the basement of Honningbrew Meadery. Through a combination of venomous compounds and magical manipulation, it was transformed into a more lethal variant of its species, likely meant to serve as a prototype for Hamelyn''s larger scheme of breeding an army of enhanced skeevers.', 'Unlike typical skeevers that flee when outmatched, Venomfang displays unusual aggression and tactical cunning, actively hunting prey rather than simply scavenging. It exhibits predatory intelligence beyond normal skeever capacity, using shadows and terrain to its advantage, and shows no fear of larger opponents.', 'Notably larger than the average skeever, with a muscular frame roughly twice the size of its common kin. Distinguished by prominent venomous fangs that protrude from its jaw and a darker, more mottled fur pattern that shows signs of alchemical mutation. Its eyes possess an unnatural greenish glow, suggesting magical alteration.', '* Hamelyn - Creator and master, though the relationship is more one of magical control than loyalty * Other Enhanced Skeevers - Pack leader among the mutated specimens * Common Skeevers - Demonstrates dominance over normal specimens * Maven Black-Briar - Indirect enemy due to her opposition to Hamelyn''s operation', 'Serves as an enhanced guard beast within Honningbrew Meadery''s basement, protecting Hamelyn''s alchemical laboratory and experimental breeding operation. Acts as both test subject and enforcer in Hamelyn''s schemes to disrupt Skyrim''s meadery business.', '* Enhanced venomous bite capable of delivering potent neurotoxins * Superior strength and agility compared to normal skeevers * Advanced hunting instincts and tactical awareness * Heightened resistance to poisons and disease * Ability to coordinate attacks with other enhanced skeevers', 'Communicates through aggressive hissing and chittering sounds that carry more menace than typical skeever vocalizations. Its calls can direct other skeevers in coordinated attacks, suggesting a primitive but effective form of pack communication.', '* Defend its territory within Honningbrew Basement from intruders * Serve its master Hamelyn''s experimental purposes * Maintain dominance over other enhanced skeevers in the pack * Spread the influence of mutated skeevers throughout Skyrim''s underground');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('slaughterfish', 'The Slaughterfish is a feared aquatic predator that dominates Skyrim''s waterways with ruthless efficiency and primal instinct. These ancient creatures have evolved to become perfect killing machines, combining lightning-fast speed with razor-sharp teeth and an unrelenting hunting drive that has earned them their notorious reputation.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maledarkelf', '', 'sk_maledarkelf', '', 'Slaughterfish have inhabited Tamriel''s waters since the Merethic Era, adapting and evolving into apex predators of the aquatic ecosystem. Their species has remained largely unchanged for thousands of years, with some scholars theorizing they may share distant ancestry with the fearsome Dreugh of the Second Era. These creatures have developed complex hunting territories throughout Skyrim''s waterways, passing down their domains through generations of offspring.', 'Slaughterfish exhibit purely predatory behavior driven by primitive instinct and territorial aggression. They show no fear of larger creatures and will relentlessly pursue prey that enters their domain, displaying a single-minded determination that borders on supernatural. Unlike other predators, they rarely retreat from confrontation and will continue attacking until either they or their target is dead.', 'A streamlined, serpentine body typically measuring 4-6 feet in length, covered in thick, overlapping scales that shimmer with a metallic gleam. Their elongated heads feature multiple rows of serrated teeth and small, dark eyes positioned for optimal hunting visibility, while their powerful tails propel them through water with exceptional speed and precision.', '* Other Slaughterfish - Typically solitary but occasionally hunt in small groups * Horkers - Natural prey animals found in coastal waters * Mudcrabs - Territorial rivals in shallow waters * Argonians - Only race capable of effectively hunting them underwater', 'Apex predator of Skyrim''s aquatic ecosystems, maintaining population control of smaller fish species and water-dwelling creatures. They serve a crucial role in the natural order by preventing overpopulation of prey species and removing weak or sick animals from the water system.', '* Exceptional swimming speed and maneuverability in water * Powerful bite force capable of crushing bone * Advanced sensory abilities to detect movement and blood in water * Natural camouflage allowing them to blend with murky depths * Ability to attack and pursue prey in both deep and shallow waters', 'Slaughterfish communicate through basic behavioral displays and movement patterns rather than vocalizations. Their presence is often only marked by the rippling of water and fleeing of smaller fish.', '* Maintain and defend established hunting territory * Secure regular prey to sustain themselves * Reproduce during spawning seasons to ensure species survival * Expand territory when opportunity presents itself');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('elk', 'A majestic creature of Skyrim''s wilderness, embodying both strength and grace through its imposing stature and swift movements. As one of the more noble beasts of the northern forests, the elk represents the untamed spirit of Skyrim''s natural world, commanding respect from hunters and travelers alike.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'maleelfhaughty', '', 'sk_maleelfhaughty', '', 'Descended from ancient megafauna that once dominated Tamriel''s northern reaches, elk have adapted perfectly to Skyrim''s harsh climate and rugged terrain. Through countless generations, they have developed keen senses and swift reflexes that allow them to thrive in territories ranging from the tundra of Winterhold to the autumn forests of the Rift.', 'Naturally cautious and alert, elk maintain a dignified demeanor that shifts instantly to focused survival instinct when threatened. Though typically solitary or found in small family groups, they display remarkable intelligence in assessing threats and choosing escape routes. During mating season, males become more territorial and aggressive, engaging in dramatic antler-clashing contests.', 'Standing significantly taller than common deer, elk possess a muscular, robust build with powerful shoulders and legs. Their most distinctive feature is their impressive rack of antlers, which can span several feet in width on mature males. Their thick fur ranges from brownish-gray to russet, with lighter coloring on their underbelly and around their face.', '* Other Elk - Forms loose social bonds, particularly during mating season and while raising young * Spriggans - Natural allies who can temporarily control elk behavior * Hunters - Natural adversaries who prize them for their meat and hide * Wolves - Primary predators who hunt them across Skyrim''s wilderness * Bears - Powerful predators they actively avoid', 'As a wild creature, the elk''s primary role is maintaining Skyrim''s ecological balance. They serve as important prey animals for predators while helping to manage forest vegetation through their grazing patterns.', '* Exceptional speed and agility, capable of quick directional changes while running * Keen senses, particularly hearing and smell, for detecting threats * Powerful swimming ability to cross rivers and lakes * Natural camouflage in both forested and snowy environments * Impressive strength displayed during mating season battles', 'Communicates through a range of vocalizations, from deep bugling calls during mating season to sharp warning snorts when danger is detected. Their body language includes subtle ear movements and tail positions that signal alertness or alarm.', '* Survive through Skyrim''s harsh seasons by finding adequate food and shelter * Successfully mate and protect offspring until maturity * Maintain territory in resource-rich areas * Avoid predators and hunters through vigilance and swift escape');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('deer', 'The deer of Skyrim embody the untamed spirit of the wilderness, representing both the fragility and resilience of nature itself. These graceful creatures serve as a vital part of Skyrim''s ecosystem, providing sustenance for predators and hunters alike while maintaining their own delicate balance through keen senses and swift flight.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malecondescending', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Deer have roamed the forests and plains of Skyrim since time immemorial, evolving alongside the land''s harsh climate and dangerous predators. Their species has adapted to survive everything from ancient Nordic hunters to modern threats, developing acute senses and remarkable speed that have allowed them to persist through countless generations.', 'Naturally cautious and alert, deer exhibit a sophisticated social awareness within their herds and a deep connection to natural rhythms. While typically docile and non-confrontational, they display remarkable courage when protecting their young or when influenced by spriggans, revealing an underlying complexity to their seemingly simple nature.', 'Adult deer stand roughly 4-5 feet tall at the shoulder, with males being slightly larger and bearing impressive antlers that can span up to 3 feet wide. Their thick fur ranges from reddish-brown to gray, with lighter undersides, and their muscular bodies are built for both speed and endurance.', '* Spriggans - Natural allies who can command deer to defend sacred groves * Other Deer - Form close-knit family groups and herds for protection * Hunters - Primary predators who seek them for resources * Wolves - Natural enemies who regularly hunt them * Bears - Dangerous predators they actively avoid', 'Deer serve as a keystone species in Skyrim''s ecosystem, maintaining forest health through grazing and providing a crucial food source for predators. They play an essential role in the natural cycle of life and death that sustains the wilderness.', '* Exceptional speed and agility, capable of outrunning most predators * Keen senses, particularly hearing and smell, to detect threats * Natural camouflage abilities that help them blend with forest surroundings * Impressive jumping capability, able to clear obstacles while fleeing * Social coordination within herds for collective survival', 'Deer communicate through a variety of vocalizations, from soft bleats to resonant bugles that echo through the forests. Their calls serve multiple purposes, from warning others of danger to attracting mates during breeding season.', '* Survive and protect their young through harsh seasons * Maintain and defend territorial breeding grounds * Preserve the natural balance of their woodland habitats * Find safe passage through hunting grounds to reach seasonal grazing areas');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('vale_deer', 'Vale Deer are mystical creatures native to the Forgotten Vale, distinguished by their luminescent pelts that emit an ethereal glow in darkness. These elusive beings represent a unique adaptation to the ancient magical environment of their home, embodying both the material and spiritual essence of this hidden realm.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malecondescending', '', 'sk_malecondescending', '', 'Vale Deer evolved in isolation within the Forgotten Vale, developing their distinctive bioluminescent qualities in response to the magical energies permeating their habitat. Their ancestors were likely common deer who became transformed over centuries of exposure to the powerful ancient magic of the Snow Elves and their forgotten civilization.', 'Though naturally timid and cautious like their common cousins, Vale Deer possess an almost supernatural awareness of their surroundings and display remarkable intelligence in evading hunters. They exhibit complex social behaviors within their herds and demonstrate an innate connection to the magical energies of their environment.', 'Vale Deer are slightly larger than common deer, with distinctive patches of luminescent fur that glow softly in darkness. Their antlers are more elaborate than those of regular deer, with delicate crystalline-like formations that catch and reflect light. Their eyes possess an opalescent quality that seems to shimmer with inner light.', '* Snow Elves - Ancient connection through shared habitat and magical influence * Spriggans - Natural allies who protect and guide the herds * Frost Giants - Occasional predators who hunt them for food * Falmer - Hostile entities who view them as prey * Other Vale Deer - Strong herd bonds and family groups', 'Vale Deer serve as both prey animals and magical conduits within their ecosystem, their presence helping to maintain the delicate magical balance of the Forgotten Vale. They act as unofficial guardians of ancient Snow Elf ruins, their movements often marking safe paths through dangerous territory.', '* Natural camouflage abilities enhanced by magical bioluminescence * Exceptional agility and speed, especially in snowy terrain * Innate magical sensitivity allowing them to detect and avoid danger * Ability to navigate treacherous terrain with supernatural sure-footedness', 'Vale Deer communicate through a series of soft calls and body language, with males producing distinctive ethereal bugling sounds during mating season. Their vocalizations often carry a haunting, almost musical quality that seems to echo with ancient magic.', '* Survive and maintain their species in their isolated habitat * Protect their young from predators and hostile entities * Preserve the magical balance of their ancestral territory * Guard the ancient secrets of the Forgotten Vale through their presence');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('fox', 'Fox is an enigmatic creature of Skyrim''s wilderness, embodying the cunning and evasive nature of its species while maintaining a mysterious presence that borders on the mythical. Unlike common foxes, this particular individual has developed an almost supernatural ability to navigate Skyrim''s harsh terrain, leading some to whisper that it might be blessed by Kynareth herself.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malekhajiit', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Born in the dense forests near Falkreath, Fox learned early the art of survival in Skyrim''s unforgiving wilderness. Through countless encounters with predators and hunters, this creature developed an uncanny intelligence that sets it apart from its kin, learning to read the intentions of both beast and humanoid alike. Years of evading capture have honed its instincts to near-legendary status.', 'Fox exhibits an extraordinary blend of curiosity and caution, often observing travelers from hidden vantage points while maintaining a safe distance. Despite its natural wariness, it shows remarkable intelligence in distinguishing friend from foe, occasionally allowing trusted individuals to catch brief glimpses before vanishing into the underbrush. Its behavior suggests a playful yet calculating nature, treating survival as both necessity and sport.', 'A sleek, red-furred creature with piercing amber eyes that seem to hold unusual wisdom. Its coat is particularly lustrous, with subtle variations in color that aid in camouflage, while its tail is notably fuller than that of common foxes. Slightly larger than the average fox, its lean muscular build speaks to years of swift escapes and careful hunting.', '* Spriggans - Natural allies who sometimes provide protection in the deepest woods * Rabbits - Preferred prey, though the chase seems more sport than sustenance * Hunters - Cautious adversaries who prize its pelt * Local Children - Occasional playmates who catch glimpses of the elusive creature * Fellow Foxes - Loose social connections, though primarily solitary', 'Fox serves as an unofficial guardian of the wilderness, its presence often warning prey animals of approaching predators. Its activities help maintain the delicate balance of Skyrim''s ecosystem, while its legendary status brings a touch of mystery to the forest.', '* Master of stealth and evasion, capable of vanishing without a trace * Expert hunter with precise tracking abilities * Remarkable agility and speed, especially in forest terrain * Keen sense of danger and ability to read intentions * Supernatural talent for finding escape routes in any situation', 'Though unable to speak in human tongues, Fox communicates through a complex series of barks, yips, and body language that convey surprising depth of meaning. Its vocalizations often carry a playful yet knowing tone, as if sharing secrets with the forest itself.', '* Maintain freedom and independence in an increasingly dangerous world * Protect its territory from unnatural threats * Continue to build its legend among the people of Skyrim * Preserve the ancient knowledge of the wild places');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('snow_fox', 'A mysterious snow fox that embodies the ethereal spirit of Skyrim''s frozen wilderness, known for its ghostlike ability to move silently through the snow-covered landscape. This elusive creature represents one of the most enigmatic wildlife specimens in Skyrim, possessing an almost supernatural ability to disappear without leaving any trace of its presence.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malekhajiit', '', 'sk_malekhajiit', '', 'Snow foxes emerged as a distinct species adapted to Skyrim''s harsh northern climate, evolving their pure white coat and silent hunting techniques over generations. Unlike their red-furred cousins, these creatures developed a deeper connection to the natural magic of Skyrim''s tundra, evidenced by their ethereal nature and inability to leave behind physical remains when slain.', 'Naturally cautious and observant, the snow fox exhibits remarkable intelligence in assessing potential threats and opportunities. While typically non-aggressive, they display fierce loyalty when bound to a Spriggan''s will or when adopted as companions by children. Their behavior suggests a complex understanding of their environment, often appearing to deliberately lead travelers astray or watch from hidden vantage points.', 'Covered in pristine white fur that perfectly matches the snowy environment, with piercing eyes that reflect an almost supernatural awareness. Smaller and more slender than their red fox cousins, they possess a ghostlike quality that makes them appear to float across the snow, with barely visible paw prints that seem to vanish moments after being made.', '* Spriggans - Mysterious connection that can turn them from peaceful creatures to aggressive guardians * Children - Potential companions when adopted through Hearthfire * Rabbits - Primary prey and natural quarry * Red Foxes - Distant cousins who share hunting grounds but maintain separate territories', 'Natural hunters of Skyrim''s wilderness, primarily pursuing rabbits and small prey across the tundra. They serve as essential members of the ecosystem, helping maintain the balance of wildlife populations in the harsh northern climate.', '* Nearly perfect camouflage in snowy environments * Silent movement across any terrain * Exceptional speed and agility when fleeing danger * Keen sense of smell and hearing for detecting threats and prey * Supernatural ability to disappear without leaving physical remains', 'Communicates through subtle body language and occasional soft vocalizations typical of canines. Their presence is often felt more than heard, with their silent observation creating an almost mystical atmosphere.', '* Survive in the harsh environment of Skyrim''s wilderness * Maintain territory and hunting grounds * Avoid detection by potential predators and hunters * Preserve their mysterious nature and connection to Skyrim''s natural magic');
INSERT INTO public.npc_templates VALUES ('rabbit', 'A small, swift creature of Skyrim''s wilderness, embodying nature''s delicate balance between survival and vulnerability. The rabbit represents the quiet persistence of life, mastering the art of evasion and stealth while playing a vital role in Skyrim''s ecosystem as both prey animal and potential companion to children.', 'animal, skyrimall', 'malebandit', '', 'sk_malebandit', '', 'Born in the wild reaches of Skyrim, the rabbit emerged from a burrow nestled beneath the roots of an ancient pine. Like countless generations before, they learned the ways of survival from their mother - the subtle vibrations that signal danger, the safest paths through the underbrush, and the sweetest patches of mountain flowers.', 'Naturally cautious and hypervigilant, the rabbit exhibits an instinctive wariness that has enabled their species'' survival. Though timid, they display remarkable resilience and adaptability, capable of thriving in diverse environments from Skyrim''s tundra to its forested regions. Their gentle nature makes them particularly suitable as pets for children, though their wild instincts never truly fade.', 'A compact, furry creature with powerful hind legs built for sudden bursts of speed and agility. Their soft fur ranges from mottled brown to grey, providing natural camouflage, while their long ears serve as both sensory organs and temperature regulators. Some specimens, particularly those found in Runoff Caverns, display unusual eye colors and strange markings on their backs.', '* Foxes - Natural predators who regularly hunt rabbits * Children - Potential companions when domesticated through Hearthfire adoption * Other Rabbits - Maintain loose social bonds with nearby warren members * Hunters - View them as prey, contributing to their ''Bunnies Slaughtered'' count * Predatory Birds - Aerial threats that rabbits must constantly watch for', 'Wild creature fulfilling the role of prey species in Skyrim''s ecosystem. They serve as a vital food source for predators while helping to maintain plant populations through their grazing habits.', '* Exceptional speed and agility, capable of quick directional changes * Master of stealth and evasion tactics * Keen senses, particularly hearing and smell * Efficient forager with knowledge of edible plants * Excellent burrowing ability for creating safe shelters', 'Communicates through body language, particularly ear positions and foot-thumping warnings to alert other rabbits of danger. Makes no vocalizations except in cases of extreme distress.', '* Survive each day by avoiding predators and finding sufficient food * Maintain awareness of safe routes and hiding spots throughout their territory * Find suitable mates during breeding seasons * Establish and defend a comfortable burrow in a safe location');
